(13, 14, 31, 737, 'Delhi', 'INDIA', 'NEW DELHI', 'president-house-422375_1280.jpg', 'president-house-422375_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Delhi, officially the National Capital Territory of Delhi, is a city and the capital territory of the Republic of India. A symbol of the country&rsquo;s rich past and thriving present, Delhi is a city where ancient and modern blend seamlessly together. It is a place that not only touches your pulse but even fastens it to a frenetic speed. Home to millions of dreams, the city takes on unprecedented responsibilities of realizing dreams bringing people closer and inspiring their thoughts. The past and the present meld seamlessly together, making centuries-old monuments a part of the city&rsquo;s daily life. Delhi is very much a history&rsquo;s child. One can have a fascinating glimpse into the past in Old Delhi, with its labyrinth of narrow lanes, old havelis, and colourful bazaars. It is home to three World Heritage monuments-Qutub Minar, Red Fort and Humayun&rsquo;s Tomb that have survived many centuries, and give an idea of architectural wonders created by emperors in the past. Central Delhi, with its tree-lined avenues, imposing structures and buildings such as the Rashtrapati Bhavan, Parliament House and India Gate, reflect Delhi&rsquo;s colonial past. Delhi&rsquo;s major festivals&mdash;namely, the International Kite Festival, Magic Festival, Itra and Sugandhi Mela, Mango Festival, Dilli ke Pakwaan, and Garden Tourism Festival are becoming an integral part of Delhi&rsquo;s cultural heritage..<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Delhi is one of the India&#39;s busiest entry points. It has a wide range of accommodation available from deluxe five star luxury hotels, with top-notch restaurants, 24-hour coffee shops, swimming pools, travel agents and shopping arcades, to middle-range hotels and guest houses offering good services and a comfortable stay, down to economical tourist lodges. There are a few Tourist Hostels, Working women&#39;s Hostels, Service Apartments, Camping Sites and Dharmashalas as well.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">1.<strong> New Delhi Airport:</strong> Indira Gandhi International Airport, situated to the southwest of Delhi, is the main gateway for the city&#39;s domestic and international civilian air traffic. It is one of the busiest airports in South Asia. A second airport open for commercial flights has been suggested either by expansion of Meerut Airport or construction of a new airport in Greater Noida.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">2.<strong> Railway Station</strong>: &nbsp;Delhi is a major junction in the Indian railway network and is the headquarters of the Northern Railway. The five main railway stations are New Delhi Railway Station, Old Delhi, Hazrat Nizamuddin Railway Station, Anand Vihar Railway Terminal and Sarai Rohilla Station.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">3.<strong> Bus Services</strong>: &nbsp;Delhi has one of India&#39;s largest bus transport systems. Buses are operated by the state-owned Delhi Transport Corporation (DTC), which owns the largest fleet of compressed natural gas (CNG)-fueled buses in the world. (DTDC, UPSRTC) are an important means of public transport in the Metro city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">4. <strong>Delhi Metro</strong>: The Delhi Metro is a rapid transit system serving Delhi, Faridabad, &nbsp;Gurgaon, Noida &nbsp;and Ghaziabad &nbsp; in the National Capital Region of India. Delhi Metro is the world&#39;s 10th largest metro system in terms of length. Delhi Metro was India&#39;s second modern public transportation system, which has revolutionised travel by providing a fast, reliable, safe, and comfortable means of transport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">4.<strong> Other Modes</strong>: The local transportation is the lifeline of the capital city of Delhi. More than half of the population in Delhi is dependent on local transport for &nbsp;commuting purposes. The means &amp; modes of transport in New Delhi are many, ranging from the Metro Trains, Local Trains, Buses, Taxies and cabs.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><br />\r\n1 - PARANTHE WALI GALI, IN CHANDNI CHOWK - (FAMOUS FOR PARATHA)<br />\r\n2 - LALA BABU CHAAT BHANDAR, IN CHANDNI CHOWK, OPP MC DONALD - (FAMOUS FOR CHAAT)<br />\r\n3 - BISHAN SWAROOP, IN CHANDNI CHOWK - (FAMOUS FOR FRUIT CHAT &amp; ALLO KULLA)<br />\r\n4 - SHREE BALAJI CHAAT BHANDAR,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;IN CHANDNI CHOWK, OLD DELHI - (FAMOUS FOR CHAT)<br />\r\n5 - KHANDANI PAKODE WALA, IN SAROJNI NAGAR RING ROAD MARKET - (FAMOUS FOR VARIETY OF PAKAODA)<br />\r\n6 - KUCHA KING,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;OPPOSITE KHANDANI PAKODE WALA - (FAMOUS FOR KULCHA)<br />\r\n7 - PRINCES PAN &amp; CHAAT CORNER,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;AT CHANDNI CHOWK - (FAMOUS FOR PAN AND CHAT)<br />\r\n8 - DILLI HUT, AT INA - (FAMOUS FOR VARIETY OF SNACKS)<br />\r\n9 - KHAN CHACHA, AT KHAN MARKET - (FAMOUS FOR KEBABS, ROLLS &amp; MUCH MORE)<br />\r\n10- SITARAM DIWAN CHAND, AT PAHARGANJ - (FAMOUS FOR CHOLE BHATURE)<br />\r\n11- BITTO TIKKIWALA, AT KAROL BAGH - (FAMOUS FOR TIKKI)<br />\r\n12- SALIMS KEBABS, IN KHAN MARKET - (FAMOUS FOR KEKORI KEBABS AND ROLLS)<br />\r\n13- DOLMA AUNTY KE MOMOS, IN LAJPAT NAGAR MARKET - (FAMOUS FOR MOMOS)<br />\r\n14- AL BAKE, IN NEW FRIENDS COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR SHAWARMA, KIND OF ROLL)<br />\r\n15- MOTI MAHAL, AT DARYAGANJ, HAVEMORE, PANDAR ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR BUTTER CHICKEN)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n16- ITC MAURYA,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;AL KAKORI, AL KAUSER, RK PURAM - (FAMOUS FOR BIRYANI)<br />\r\n17- DEEZ BIRYANI, AT DEFENCE COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR KEBABS)<br />\r\n18- GIANI DI HATTI, AT CHANDNI CHOWK - (FAMOUS FOR DESERT)<br />\r\n19- NATRAJ, AT CHANDNI CHOWK - (FAMOUS FOR DAHI BHALLA)<br />\r\n20- PANDIT BABU RAM DEVI DAYAL, IN PARANTHE WALI GALI, CHANDNI CHOWK - (FAMOUS FOR PARATHA)<br />\r\n21- DULI CHAND NARESH GUPTA, IN SITARAM BAZAR NR. CHAWRI BAZAR, SOUTH OF CHANDNI CHOWK - (FAMOUS FOR KULFI)<br />\r\n22- SHYAM SWEETS, IN CHAWRI BAZAR - (FAMOUS FOR BEDMI ALOO, NAGORI HALWA)<br />\r\n23- KARIM HOTEL&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;NEAR JAMA MASJID, OLD DELHI - (FAMOUS FOR MUTTON BURRA KEBAB)<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '3,8,9,10,11,12,16,19,25,26,31,32'),
(20, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'AGRA', 'india-367_1280.jpg', 'india-866692_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Agra is a district in Uttar Pradesh, located along the banks of Yamuna River and is a home to many monuments and the famous wonder TAJ MAHAL and is one of the most frequently visited cities by tourists throughout the year.Believed to have been built in 1475, Agra even finds a mention in the epic Mahabharatha where it is called Agraban (meaning paradise).Aside from the Taj Mahal, Agra has 2 other UNESCO World Heritage Sites: Agra Fort &amp; Fatehpur Sikri.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Agra being one of the favourite places for tourists offers variety of option from budget to luxury easily available all across the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Airport</strong> - Air Force Station Agra at VIP Rd, Ajeet Nagar Gate, Kheria Mode, Ajeet Nagar, Idgah Colony, serves the city. Another major airport close to city is Indra Gandhi International Airport, Delhi about 219 kms from Agra.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Railway Station</strong> - &nbsp;The main riailway juction that erves the city is Agra Cantt - North Central Railways. Other railway stations in agra are Raja ki Mandi (North Central Railways), Agra Fort (North Central Railways), Agra City (North Central Railways), Idgah (North Central Railways), Yamuna Bridge (North Central Railways).</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Bus Service</strong> - Intra State Bus Service is easily available from the Bus Stand is in Idgah Colony very close to both the Idgah Railway Station as well as the Agra Cantt,Uttar Pradesh State Road Transport Corporation (UPSRTC) operates hi-tech, deluxe, semi-deluxe and ordinary buses from here. Other private luxury bus services are alo avialable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Other Modes</strong> - Taxis, Auto rickshaws and Car hire services (like Ola, Uber etc.) are also available within the city.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><br />\r\n1- DASAPRAKASH - (FAMOUS FOR SOUTH INDIAN CUSINE)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - ESPHAHAN (ADVANCE RESERVATION IS COMPULSORY HERE), INSIDE THE OBERAI AMARVILAS, TAJ RESORT GATE - (FAMOUS FOR ELEGANT CUSINE)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - SHANKAR JI (SNACK BAR), AT SHRI GANPAT LAL GUPTA MARG - (FAMOUS FOR LOCAL CUSINE)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center">3 - PINCH OF SPICE, AT FATEHABAD ROAD, AGRA (FAMOUS FOR NON VEG DISHES)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center">4 - JAHAPANAH, E-23, SHOPPING ARCADE SADAR BAZAR - (FAMOUS FOR AWADHI CUSINE LIKE BIRYANI, GALAWATI KEBABS ETC)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n5 - JHANKAR (WITH MUSIC AND DANCING ALL NIGHT), TAJ VIEW HOTEL, FATEHABAD ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR INDIAN CUSINE)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n6 - STUFFMAKERS (ON A ROOF TOP AT HOTEL KAMAL),&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;AT HOTEL KAMAL SOUTH GATE, TAJ GANJ - (FAMOUS FOR INDIAN CUSINE)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center">7 - PANCHI PETHA, OPP. HEERA TALKIES BY PASS ROAD AGRA - (FAMOUS FOR VAREITY OF PETHA, SWEET)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n8 - DEVIRAM HALWAI - [FAMOUS FOR JALEBI AND BEDAI (FRIED BREAD)]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n9 - BHAGAT HALWAI - (FAMOUS FOR BHALLA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n10 - GMB SWEETS&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;- (FAMOUS FOR JALEBI)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '6,8,16,19,25'),
(25, 14, 31, 1657, 'Chhattisgarh', 'INDIA', 'JASHPUR', 'creek-21749_1920.jpg', 'creek-21749_19201.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Jashpur is a city situated in the north east of the Indian state of Chhattisgarh adjoining the border of Jharkhand and Odisha, the city has dense forests, hills and mountains, some of the mountains runs parallel to each other and valleys that shows the natural beauty of the city. Jashpur is very well connected with the major cities of Chhattisgarh through a netwok of roads.&nbsp;The City is not very big but many beautiful and has many places for tourists to explore.</p>\r\n', '<p>Accomodation facility is average in the with not so many options available in the city.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Airport</strong>- The nearest airport to Jashpur city is Raipur Airport. Frequent flights from various cities to Raipur is directly available and their from one can reach to Jashpur by road very easily.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Railway</strong>- The nearest railway station to Jashpur city is Raigarh junstion. Frequent trains from other cities to Raigarh is directly available and their from one can reach to Jashpur by road very easily.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Bus Service</strong> - &nbsp;Intra State and Intra City Bus Services are available from&nbsp;Jashpur Bus Stand.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Other Modes</strong> - Auto Rickshwas and taxis are easily&nbsp;available in the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - GOSWAMI RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT JASHPUR NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - INDIAN CHAAT CENTER, &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT JASHPUR NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR PANIPURI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - SANTOSH HOTEL, LOCATED AT PATHALGAON - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA AND BADA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - KOLKATA BIRYANI CENTER, LOCATED AT PATHALGAON - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN BIRYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - CAFE MARINE DRIVE FOOD POINT, LOCATED AT FIRST FLOOR, PRATAPPUR ROAD, AMBIKAPUR - (FAMOUS FOR MASALA COLDRINK)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '6,8,17,19,20,24'),
(26, 14, 31, 1657, 'Chhattisgarh', 'INDIA', 'KORIYA', 'perspective-688562_1920.jpg', 'perspective-688562_19201.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Koriya is a district in the state of Chhattisgarh, lies in the north-western part of the state. The place is full of dense forests, mountains, rivers and waterfalls. Languages spoken in the district are Bagheli and hindi. District Koriya is surrounded by Sirdhi district in the north and Anuppur dstrict in the west are districts of Madhya Pradesh and Korba district in south and Surguja district in the east are districts of Chhattisgarh.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>The accomdation facility of hotels budget to luxury with modern ameneties is avialable all across the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<div id="cke_pastebin" style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Airport </strong>- The nearest airport to the district is Raipur airport which lies around 364 km from the district.</div>\r\n\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Railway</strong> - The nearest railway station that serves the city is the Bilaspur Junction.</div>\r\n\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Bus Service </strong>- Bus services are easily availbale in the city from &nbsp;Local Bus Stand</div>\r\n\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;"><br />\r\n<strong>Other Modes</strong> - Taxis and Auto rickshaw services are also available within the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - HORILAL RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT STATION ROAD, MANENDRAGARH - (FAMOUS FOR JALEBI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - JAFFRUL BIRYANI CENTRE, LOCATED AT CHURCHA MAIN ROAD, CHURCHA COLLIERY, SARDI - (FAMOUS FOR BIRYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - GREEN PARK RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT NH 78, CHAINPUR, MANENDRAGARH - (FAMOUS FOR CHILLY CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - CHAAT CHATORE MANENDRAGARH, LOCATED AT CENTRAL BANK ROAD, WARD NO 20, MOHARPARA, MANENDRAGARH - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA &nbsp;AND CHAATS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - RAJESH FAST FOOD, LOCATED AT MANENDRAGARH - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;ROLLS AND CHOWMIEN)</strong></p>\r\n', '6,17,19'),
(27, 14, 31, 1657, 'Chhattisgarh', 'INDIA', 'MAHASAMUND', 'australia-1343299_1280.jpg', 'australia-1343299_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Mahasamund is a city in the Indian state of Chhattisgarh.District Mahasamund is surrounded by Nuapara district and Bargarh dstrict of Orissa state and Raipur district and Raigarh district of Chhattisgarh state.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>The accomdation facility of hotels budget to luxury with modern ameneties is avialable all across the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Airport</strong> - The nearest airport to Mahasamund district is Raipur airport which lies around 39 km from the city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Railway</strong> - The city is served by Mahasamund Railway Station of the East Coast Railway Zone of the Indian Railways.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Bus Service</strong> - Intra State and city bus serviace are availbale from bus stand.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Other Modes</strong> - Taxis and Auto rickshaw services are also available within the city.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - GOLI VADA PAV, LOCATED AT NEAR GANESH TEMPLE, BARONDA CHOWK - (FAMOUS FOR VADA PAV)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - SONI MISTHAN BHANDAR, LOCATED AT MAHASAMUND - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSAS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - KAMTA, LOCATED AT OLD CIVIL LINES, SUBASH NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR BHELPURI)</strong></p>\r\n', '6,19'),
(29, 14, 31, 1657, 'Chhattisgarh', 'INDIA', 'KANKER', 'mountain-1504197_1920.jpg', 'mountain-1504197_19201.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kanker is a ditrict in the Indian state of Chhattisgarh, situated iin the southern region of the state. The district is located in between Raipur and Jagdalpur the two well developed cities of state Chhattisgarh. Kanker became an independent district in the year 1999, earlier it was a part of old Bastar District. The main languages spoken in the district are Hindi, Bengali, Chhattisgarhi, Gondi and Halbi. The headquarters of Kanker district is around 155 km approx. from Jagdalpur and 145 km approx from Raipur. May is the hottest and December is the coldest month in the district, climate in the district is of monsoon type.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>The accomdation facility is average and&nbsp;few hotels and lodges are avialable all across the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Airport</strong> - The nearest airport to Kanker district is Raipur airport which lies around 125 km approx. from the city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Railway</strong>- The nearest railway station to Kanker Diastrict is Dhamtari Railway Station of the South East Central Railway Zone of the Indian Railways.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Bus Services</strong> - Intra State and city bus services are available from bus stand.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Other Modes</strong> - Taxis and Auto rickshaw services are also available within the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - HOTEL SUNDARAM, LOCATED AT MANZAPARA - (FAMOUS FOR DAAL FRY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - MAKDI DABA, LOCATED AT STATE HIGHWAY 22, MAKRIKHUNA - (FAMOUS FOR DOSA AND KHEER)</strong></p>\r\n', '6,17,18'),
(31, 14, 31, 1657, 'Chhattisgarh', 'INDIA', 'DANTEWADA', 'children-428909_6401.jpg', 'children-428909_6402.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Dantewada is one of the most beautiful and picturesque districts of Chhattisgarh, located in the famous and enchanting Bastar region. Also one of the famous ancient towns of India, Dantewada had been the capital city of a glorious Kingdom in its golden past. Known as Tarlapal and Dantawali in pre historical days, and named after Goddess Danteshwari, an incarnate of Shakti, this district in Bastar region is known for its scenic beauty, rivers and for its historical importance. Dantewada offers you all natural elements from Hills Mountains to rivers and hence creating complete sceneries. It also houses recently developed stretch of Rowghat mines. However, this area is affected by Naxalism and it is advisable to research properly about the recent events before heading out to Dantewada. Dantewada is blessed with exceptionally beautiful natural landscapes comprising of scenic hills and valleys, lush green sal and teak forests and young and lively rivers. Indravati, Godavari, Shabhari, Shankhini and Dankiny rivers flow all through the length and breathe of Dantewada. All these rivers with many enchanting waterfalls provide a unique charm to Dantewada, making it one of the loveliest destinations in Chhattisgarh. Apart from its scenic beauty, Dantewada also has a number of beautiful temples and important historical sites, worth visiting on your tours to Chhattisgarh.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Dantewada offers few luxury and budget hotels complete with arrangements for food.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air </strong>- Raipur Airport is the nearest airport to reach Dantewada city.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail </strong>- Dantewada Railway Station has its own railway station which is a part of the south east Railway zone and runs a regular passenger train from Vizag to Bailadila town which passes through Araku Valley, and stops for a while at Dantewada station before reaching Bailadila.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Bus </strong>- Dantewada is well connected by regular bus services. To reach the city tourists can avail regular private luxury and CSRTC bus services which are available from almost all the big cities of Chhattisgarh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road </strong>- Dantewada is well connected with other cities within Chhattisgarh such as Bastar and Koraput. It is located along State Highway 16, which makes it easier for tourists to travel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Buses and autos are the preferred modes of travel.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>DANTEWADA - {FAMOUS FOR CHECH BHAJI IS A DISH MADE FROM CURD, BADI OR WADI (BLACK GRAM LENTILS), GARLIC- 7 CLOVES, CHOPPED DRY RED CHILLY ; BOHAR BHAJI IS A DISH MADE FROM GRAM PULSES, RED CHILLY POWDER, CORIANDER, TURMERIC POWDER AND BUTTERMILK ; BAFAURI IS A SWEET MADE FROM CHANNA DAL}</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '17,18'),
(35, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'ALLAHABAD', 'sangam.JPG', 'sangam1.JPG', '<p style="text-align:justify">Allahabad is among most populous city of Uttar Pradesh also known as Prayag &lsquo;Place of Sacrifice&rsquo; is of huge Religious Importance for Hindu and is situated in the confluence of three holy rivers Ganga, Yamuna and mythical Saraswati and is also called Sangam Nagri were Mahkumbh is held every twelve year, Ardha kumbh every six year, which is known to be world&rsquo;s biggest fair and largest gathering of people. Allahabad is 2<sup>nd</sup> oldest city in India. Allahabad is also referred to be &ldquo;City of Green Gold&rdquo; for its variety of guavas. Allahabad is also known as city of Prime Ministers as seven out fifteen Prime ministers of India since Independence have connections to Allahabad in some or other way. Allahabad is also referred as Tirth Raj. As per writing of Padam Puran &ndash; &ldquo;As sun is amongst the moon &amp; the moon is amongst the stars, like wise Prayag is best among all places of Pilgrimage.Allahabad University is forth oldest University in India and is of great educational importance.</p>\r\n', '<div id="cke_pastebin">Hotels in Allahabad are available in sufficient numbers in all categories ranging from luxury to economical. Other facilities like Oyo Rooms etc. are also available now-a-days.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n', '<div id="cke_pastebin" style="text-align: justify;">1.&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>&nbsp;Allahabad Airport</strong>: The airport is 12 kilometres from the city centre and lies in Bamrauli.</div>\r\n\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">2.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Railway Station</strong>: The four major railway stations in Allahabad are Prayag Station, City station at Rambagh, Daraganj Station and Allahabad Junction.</div>\r\n\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">3.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Bus Services</strong>: Buses operated by Uttar Pradesh State Road Transport Corporation&nbsp;(UPSRTC) are an important means of public transport in the metro.</div>\r\n\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">4.&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>&nbsp;Other Modes</strong>: Auto Rikshaws have been a popular mode of transportation. E-rickshaws &nbsp;have also been introduced and quickly spread over the city. Renowned taxi firms like Ola Cabs, Taxi For Sure etc. are also operating in the city, making transportation in the city more hassle-free &amp; convenient. Cycle-&nbsp;Rickshaws are the most economical means of transportation.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - HARI KE SAMOSE - &nbsp; AT LOKNATH ANE, CHOWK- (FAMOUS FOR SANCKS &amp; SPICES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 -&nbsp;NETRAM - &nbsp;AT&nbsp;NETRAM CHAURAHA, GEORGE TOWN, ALLAHABAD - &nbsp;(FAMOUS FOR KACHORI SABZI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - HIRA HALWAI - AT&nbsp;CIVIL LINES, GT ROAD - {FAMOUS FOR GULABJAMUN (SWEET)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - BHAGWANDAS - &nbsp;NEAR ZERO ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR MOTICHOOR KE LADOO)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - SANIK -&nbsp;&nbsp;IN ASHOK NAGAR -&nbsp;(FAMOUS FOR CHOLE SAMOSE &amp; SWEET)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - LALLU PAN CORNER -&nbsp;IN CIVIL LINES - &nbsp;(FAMOUS FOR MASALA COLD DRINK AND PAN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7- RAJA RAM - IN&nbsp;LOKNATH LANE, CHOWK - (FAMOUS FOR RABRI AND KULFI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - DEHATI - IN&nbsp;SOHBATIYABAGH, NEAR CMP DEGREE COLLAGE - (FAMOUS FOR RASGULLA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>9 -&nbsp;SULAKI - IN&nbsp;SULAKI CROSSING, BAHADURGANJ - {FAMOUS FOR JALEBI (SWEET DISH)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>10 - MEDICAL CHAAT CORNER - AT MEDICAL CROSSING - {FAMOUS FOR CHAAT (SPICY SNACK)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>11 -&nbsp;RADHE - IN&nbsp;LOKNATH LANE, CHOWK - (FAMOUS FOR FRUIT CREAM)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>12 -&nbsp;SOFIA PAN CORNER - AT&nbsp;SUBHASH CHAURAHA - (FAMOUS FOR GILORY PAN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>13 -&nbsp;KADHENU SWEETS - AT&nbsp; MG MARG CIVIL LINES - (FAMOUS FOR VARIETY OF SWEETS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center">&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '2,6,8,10,11,16,26,30'),
(36, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'MORADABAD', 'beer-barrel-956322_640.jpg', 'beer-barrel-956322_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Widely known as &ldquo;The Brass City&rdquo;, Moradabad is known worldwide for its high quality brass handicrafts that are exported all over the world particularly in the Europe and the North America. Also known as the &ldquo;City of Nakshatra&rdquo;, Moradabad is located in the state of Uttar Pradesh and is situated on the banks of River Ramganga. Moradabad Travel guide is incomplete without a mention of its spiritual legacy and rich heritage. Moradabad has also added its name in the field of music and education.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">i). Sambhal&nbsp;<br />\r\nThe district was created by the state government on 23 July 2012 as one of three new districts in the state. At the time of its creation, the state government decided to name the new district &quot;Bhimnagar&quot; in honour of Bhimrao Ambedkar. The district of Sambhal is part of the Moradabad division Uttar Pradesh state.The town of Sambhal is its headquarters. It was a prominent town during the medieval period.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">ii). Chandausi&nbsp;<br />\r\nChandausi is a city and a municipal board in Sambhal district in the state of Uttar Pradesh, India. The original name of the city was &quot;Chaand Si&quot;, meaning &quot;moon-like&rdquo;.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Moradabad has many deluxe and medium to budget accommodation options.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">1.<strong> Moradabad Airport</strong>: The nearest Domestic Airport from Moradabad is &lsquo;Pantnagar Airport&rsquo;, roughly 85 Kms. from Moradabad and is well connected to Delhi.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">2. <strong>Railway Station</strong>: The Railway Station lies at the centre of the city and is well connected to many major cities of India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">3. <strong>Bus Service</strong>: Local And Inter-State buses are available all the time from the Local Bus&nbsp;Stand. Various privately run luxury buses are also available.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">4. <strong>Other Modes</strong>: Taxis, Auto rickshaws and Car hire services (like Ola, Uber etc.) are also&nbsp;available within the city.</p>\r\n', '<p>1 - NANDAN SWEETS - IN MOORADABAD - (FAMOUS FOR VARIETY OF SWEETS)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2 - EMPEROR (FINE DINNING RESTAURANT IN HOTEL HOLIDAY REGENCY) - ON DEHLI ROAD, NH- 24, (FAMOUS FOR VARIETY OF DISHES)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3 - VICTORIA RESTAURANT - IN MOORADABAD - (FAMOUS FOR VARIETY OF DISHES)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4 - TASTY BITES - IN HOTEL PARK SQUARE, DEHLI ROAD, MAJHOLA - (FAMOUS FOR VARIETY OF SNACKS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '2,6,9'),
(38, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'GHAZIABAD', 'lotus-pond-380684_640.jpg', 'lotus-pond-380684_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The district of Ghaziabad is situated in the middle of Ganga-Yamuna doab in Uttar Pradesh.&nbsp;it acts as the main entrance of Uttar Pradesh and that is why it is also called the GATEWAY OF Uttar Pradesh. &nbsp;It is a part of National Capitol Region of Delhi and is major industrial and educational centre. Mythologically, some neighbouring towns and villages of the city including Garhmukteshwr. Pooth Village and Ahar region have been associated with the&nbsp;Mahabharat&nbsp;and the fort at&nbsp;Loni, is associated with the legend of Lavanasura of the&nbsp;Ramayan&nbsp;period.&nbsp;Ghaziabad district is a largely suburban district of Uttar Pradesh state in northern India of National Capital Region. The town of Ghaziabad is the administrative headquarters of the district; it is the third most populous district of Uttar Pradesh. Ghaziabad, lies on the Grand Trunk road about a mile east of the Hindon river. Ganga, Yamuna and Hindon are the main rivers flowing through the district and they are filled with water throughout the year. &nbsp;Other than these there are some small rainfed rivers, prominent among them is the Kali River. Apart from these rivers the Ganga Canal flows through the district and irrigation work is carried out through different branches of Canal. The Ganga canal also caters the drinking water needs of the people of Ghaziabad as well as Delhi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">i). Modinagar<br />\r\nModinagar is a city and a municipal board in Ghaziabad district. It is approximately 45 kilometres north-east of New Delhi. It is approximately equally distant from Meerut and Ghaziabad because this city is situated at mid-way on Ghaziabad. It is best known as the home of Modi Mills. In recent years, Modinagar has been developed as an educational hub as many new institutions are being established in and around the city due to its location in National Capital Region.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">ii). Loni<br />\r\nLoni is a city in Ghaziabad District of Uttar Pradesh State. It is located 17 KM towards west from District head quarters Ghaziabad. This Place is in the border of the Ghaziabad District and North Delhi District. North Delhi District North Delhi is west towards this place. Also it is in the Border of other district Delhi. It is near to the Delhi State Border.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">iii). Hapur<br />\r\nHapur is a city in, as well as the headquarters of Hapur district, in Western Uttar Pradesh, Located about 60 kilometres East of New Delhi, the city is part of the National Capital Region (NCR). It is undergoing changes for development into a fully realised district. Soon it will be well developed and more administrative facilities will be available. It had been part of Ghaziabad district.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">iv). Khora<br />\r\nKhora is a village panchayat located in the Ghaziabad district of Uttar-Pradesh. The other nearest state capital from Khora is Delhi and its distance is 20.7 KM. Hinduism is majority religion in Khora. The major Caste of Khora is Gujjar(Baisla) and Yadavs. Islam is second most popular religion in city of Khora.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Experience the best of hospitality as you make reservations at the available budget to luxury&nbsp;hotels during your visit. Other services like PG&rsquo;s, OYO rooms are also available.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">a). <strong>Bus Service</strong>: Buses run at frequent intervals from here to Delhi, Meerut, Aligarh, Bulandshahr, Moradabad, Lucknow and to other districts also.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">b).<strong>Railway</strong>: Ghaziabad Central Station and Anand Vihar Terminal Station are an important &nbsp;stations of Northern Central Railway.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">c).<strong> Airport</strong>: The nearest airport is the Indira Gandhi International Airport which is about 45 Kms. away.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">d). <strong>Metro Rail Service</strong>: The Delhi Metro extends to Dilshad Garden station which is situated at the Apsara Border. It serves the areas of Shalimar Garden,&nbsp;Rajendra&nbsp; &nbsp; nagar, New Bus Stand Ghaziabad and other neighbouring&nbsp;Colonies. Another station exists at Vaishali, which serves that area as well as &nbsp;Vasundhara and Indirapuram, and there is also a station&nbsp;at Kaushambi.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:279pt">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="height:15.0pt; width:279pt">\r\n			<p>PANDIT DHABA-</p>\r\n\r\n			<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:230pt">\r\n				<tbody>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td style="height:15pt; width:230pt">(FAMOUS FOR NORTH INDIAN CUSINES)</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n				</tbody>\r\n			</table>\r\n\r\n			<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:155pt">\r\n				<tbody>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td style="height:15pt; width:155pt">AT SHAKTI KHAND, NEAR HANUMAN MANDIR, INDRAPURAM</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n				</tbody>\r\n			</table>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:279pt">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="height:15.0pt; width:279pt">\r\n			<p><br />\r\n			GULABWALA</p>\r\n\r\n			<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:230pt">\r\n				<tbody>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td style="height:15.0pt; width:230pt">\r\n						<p>(FAMOUS FOR VARIETY OF DESERTS AND CUSINES)</p>\r\n\r\n						<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:155pt">\r\n							<tbody>\r\n								<tr>\r\n									<td style="heigh