(40, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'LUCKNOW', 'lucknow.jpg', 'lucknow1.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Lucknow city is popularly known as the &lsquo;City of Nawabs&rdquo; situated on the banks of river Gomti. Lucknow the capital of Uttar Pradesh, was founded by Nawab Asaf-ud-Daula. Lucknow is the largest city of Uttar Pradesh with the highest Shia Muslim population in India accessible from every part of India by air, rail and road. &nbsp;It is said that Lakshmana, who was the brother of Lord Rama, laid the foundation of the ancient city and it has always been a multicultural city. The era of the Nawabs bestowed Lucknow with the courteous culture as well as mouth watering delicacies for which it is famous today. The city has a magical charm surrounding it. Be its delicious cuisine or its heart melting culture, the city leaves an everlasting impression on its visitors.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>City is having wide range of accomodation facility ranging from budget to luxury with all modern&nbsp;amenities and facilities easily available all across the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Airport</strong> - Chaudhary Charan Singh International Airport in Amausi, Lucknow serves the city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Railway Station</strong> - Is in Charbagh, south of city and is one of the busiest raiway station &amp; well connected to all major cities of India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Bus Service</strong> - Local And Inter-State buses are available all the time from the Local Bus Stand in Charbagh. Various privately run luxury buses are also available.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Other Modes</strong> - Auto, Cycle Rickshaws, Taxis on Hire (like ola, meru etc) are also available and soon the city will be connected with metro trains.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1- TUNDEY KE KABAB