US FOR KORMA AND SHAMI KEBAB)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>15 - MR. BROWN,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;AT GOMTI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR BAKED GUJIYA AND OTHER BAKERY PRODUCTS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>16 - CHAPPAN BHOG, 211-212, APNA BAZAR, SADAR BAZAR CANTONMENT - (FAMOUS FOR SWEETS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>17 - OTHER LOCAL DELECIES THAT ONE MUST TRY IN CITY ARE PAYA KI NIHARI, MALAI KI GILLORI, SHEERMAL (SWEET NAN), GALAWATI KEBAB, ROGAN JOSH (SOFT MEAT IN SPICY CURRY)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '6,8,9,10,19,27'),
(41, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'KANPUR', 'ka1.JPG', 'ka11.JPG', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kanpur is one of the major cities in the Indian state of UttarPradesh, formerly kanpur was spelled as &#39;Cawnpore&#39;. Kanpur is the second largest Industrial town in northern India. Kanpur is now a major industrial hub in north India, following India. Kanpur is the 12th most popular city in India. The city Kanpur is situated on the banks of the River Ganga, and due to its strategic location the traders started setting up factories in the city. Kanpur is the largest city in Uttar Pradesh and 5th largest in India. Kanpur is known as the Leather city of the world and it is the Economic Capital of Uttar Pradesh. The best time to visit Kanpur is between October to March. &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The city offers wide range of accomdation facility from Resorts, hotels budget to luxury with all the modern ameneties are easily avialable all across the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Airport</strong> - The city is served by Kanpur Airport situated in Chakeri, Kanpur.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Railway Station</strong> - The city is served by Kanpur Central railway station it comes under North Central Railway Zone of the Indian Railways. Kanpur Central Junction is the third busiest railway station in India. The Kanpur Central Junction is well connected with the extensive network of Indian Railways across the country. The city is also served by 14 other small stations within the boundaries of Kanpur. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Bus Service</strong> - The city is served with AC and non AC buses for local transportation within the city by Kanpur Metropolitian Bus Service.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Other Modes</strong> - Taxis, Auto rickshaws and Car hire services are also available within the city.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - THAGGU KE LADDU, SHOP NO. 1-2, MALL ROAD, BADA CHAURAHA, NEAR URSHLA EMERGENCY, CIVIL LINES - [FAMOUS FOR LADOO (SWEET)]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - MUNNA SAMOSA, NANDLAL CHAURAHA - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA &amp; VARIETY OF STREET FOOD)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - DEEP CHAUHAN DHABA,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;BHAUNTI PRATAPPUR, KANPUR - (FAMOUS FOR NORTH INDIAN CUISINE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - PALATE MULTI-CUISINE RESTAURAT , AT RAVE MOTI MALL - (FAMOUS FOR MULTI CUISINE)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n5 - PANDIT, AT MG PARK, TAGORE ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR VEG FOOD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - HANUMAN CHAT BHANDAR, AT ARADHANA COMPLEX, KAKADEO - (FAOMUS FOR CHAAT)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - MITHAS SWEETS, AT SWAROOP NAGAR, NEAR KHANNA MOTOR - (FAMOUS FOR DESERT AND VARIETY OF SNACKS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - TREATS, AT NAVEEN MARKET - (FAMOUS FOR CHINESE AND CONTINENTAL)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n9 - JANWADIS, AT KIDWAI NAGAR MARKET - (FAMOUS FOR STREET FOOD)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n10 - EMCHAT CAFE, AT MALL ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR VARIETY OF SNACKS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>11 - SAMRAT CHOLE BHATURE, AT GOVIND NAGAR ROAD, FAZALGANJ - (FAMOUS FOR CHOLE BHATURE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>12 - BUDHSEN SWEET HOUSE, AT BIRHANA ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR VARIETY OF DESERTS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>13 - HANUMAN KACHORI, AT RAWATPUT CROSSING - (FAMOUS FOR SANCKS)</strong></p>\r\n', '6,11,19,22,31');
