(45, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'GORAKHPUR', 'industry-486877_1280.jpg', 'industry-486877_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Gorakhpur is one of the major and laegest city with rich cultural and historical importance in the Indian state of UttarPradesh. The city is located along the banks of river Rapti, and the city is very close to Nepal border. The city Gorakhpur is named after Guru Gorakshnath a saint that performed &ldquo;Hath Yoga&rdquo; where now exists the Gorakhnath Temple which is one of the major tourist attraction of the city. The city is also famous for Chauri Chaura Incident during British. Gorakhpur city is the place where famous Indian Revolutionary Ram Prasad Bismil was hanged by Britishers for Kakori Train Robbery case.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The city offers wide range of accomdation facility from Resorts, hotels budget to luxury with all the modern ameneties are easily avialable all across the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Airport</strong> - The city is served by Gorakhpur Airport situated around 8 kms. from the city Gorakhpur. The airport offers limited number of commercial flights to Delhi airport only.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Railway Station</strong> - The city is served by Gorakhpur railway station it comes under North Eastern Railway Zone of the Indian Railways. The Gorakhpur Railway Junction is well connected with the extensive network of Indian Railways across the country. The city is also served by 10 other small stations within the boundaries of Gorakhpur. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Bus Service</strong> - The city is served with Taxis and Tempo Service.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Other Modes</strong> - Auto rickshaws and Car hire services are also available within the city.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center">1 - CHOUDHARY HOTEL, NEAR CITY MALL - (FAMOUS FOR SWEETS)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center">2 - BOBI&#39;S RESTAURANT, AT GOLGHAR - (FAMOUS FOR PASTRIES AND CAKES)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - MIRCH MASALA, NEAR RAILWAY STATION - (FAMOUS FOR CHAAT)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n5 - GORAKHPUR, IN CITY - (FAMOUS FOR TANGI KANJI BADA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n6 - CUISINE, IN CITY - (FAMOUS FOR GALAWAT KEBABS)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center">7 - CUISINE, NEAR GOLGHAR - (FAMOUS FOR KAKORI KEBABS)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center">8 - CUISINE, NEAR GOLGHAR - (FAMOUS FOR TANDOORI FOOD)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '6,11'),
(52, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'VARANASI', 'varanasi-1370505_1920.jpg', 'varanasi-787731_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Varanasi a city as old as time,the district in Uttar Pradesh is located along the banks of Holy River Ganga &amp; is the oldest living city in the world. Varanasi is also known as &ldquo;Kashi&rdquo; and holds high religious importance especially for Hindu, Buddhist and Jain Community. It is also known as Spritual Capital of India.Varanasi grew as an important industrial centre, famous for its muslin and silk fabrics, perfumes, ivory works, and sculpture. Buddha is believed to have founded Buddhism here around 528 BC when he gave his first sermon.Both Hindus and non-Hindus from around the world visit Varanasi for different reasons. Although Varanasi is popularly called the city of Shiva and Ganga, it is also the city of temples, the city of &#39;ghats&#39;, the city of music, and the center for moksha.<br />\r\n&quot;Older than history, older than tradition, older even than legend, And looks twice as old as all of them put together &quot; - Mark Twain.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Being one othe most visited tourist palces offers wide range of accomodation from budget to luxury including all the modern amenities and facilities easily accesible across the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Airport</strong> - Lal Bahadur Shastri International airport serves the city and is 26 kms northeast of Varanasi in Babatpur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Railway Station</strong> - Varanasi Cantonment Railway Station is the main railway station that serves the city. Another is Manduadih Terminal station of Varanasi &amp; is 4 kms from vranasi cant railway station.Some other important railway stations in Varanasi are Sarnath, Bhulanpur, Shivpur, Babatpur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Bus Service</strong> - Inter-State buses are available all the time from the Local Bus Stand at &nbsp;Vijay Nagar Colony, Chetganj. Various privately run luxury buses are also available. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Other Modes</strong> -Taxis, Auto rickshaws, Cycle rickshaws and Car hire services (like Ola, taxi for sure etc.) are also available within the city.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1- DEEPAK TAMBUL BHANDAR, NEAR DASHASHVAMEDH GHAT - [FAMOUS FOR PAAN (Mouth Freshner)]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - SHIV LASSI BHANDAR,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;IN RAM NAGAR, VISHVANATH GALI - (FAMOUS FOR BLUE LASSI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - SHRIBANDHU SWEETS, NEAR KACHORI GALI - (FAMOUS FOR SWEETS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - PATHAK JI STALL, IN VISHWANATH GALI - (FAMOUS FOR THANDAI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n5 - DEENA CHAT BHANDAR,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;IN RAMPURA, LUXA - (FAMOUS FOR CHAT)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n6 - KACHORI GALI - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORI &amp; SNACKS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n7 - PIZZERIA VATIKA CAF&Eacute;, AT ASSI GHAT - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n8 - PHULWARI, IN BACK OF ANCIENT KALI TEMPLE, NEAR BRIGHT STUDO, GODOWLIYA - (FAMOUS FOR VARIETY OF DISHES)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n9 - KESHARI RUCHIKAR BYANJAN - (FAMOUS FOR VARIETY OF DISHES)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '6,8,11,16,19,28,29'),
(71, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'MATHURA', 'altar-1119221_1920.jpg', 'altar-1119221_19201.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The city of Mathura, in Uttar Pradesh, is located 140 km south-east of Delhi and 60 km north-west of Agra. Mathura is an important place of pilgrimage in India as it is the birth place of Lord Krishna. The land of Braj starts from Kotban near Hodel about 95 km from Delhi and ends at Runakuta which is known specially for its association with the poet Surdas, an ardent Krishna devotee. Mathura is one of the most sacred cities of Hinduism and is situated on the western banks of the Yamuna River. &nbsp;Every square foot of Mathura-Vrindavan is dedicated in timeless devotion to Lord Krishna. Vrindavan &nbsp;is a town in the Mathura district of Uttar Pradesh, India. It is the site where according to Hinduism, Lord Krishna spent his childhood days. The town is about 11 km away from Mathura, is a town in the Mathura district of Uttar Pradesh, India. The town hosts many temples dedicated to the worship of Radha and Krishna.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The accomdation facility is not that good in Mathura Vrindavan due to lack of &nbsp;sufficient luxury hotels &amp; does not have high quality hotels. However, it has nearly 200 dharamsalas that are clean and affordable.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Airport - The nearest international airport to Mathura is located in Delhi, at a distance of 147 km while the closest domestic airport is Kheria airport, Agra.<br />\r\nRailway Station - Mathura Station Railway Junction at Mayur Vihar, Mathura serves the city of Mathura and Vrindavan.&nbsp;<br />\r\nBus Service - Intra State Bus service available easily from New Bus Stand at Hathras-Mathura Rd, Adarsh Nagar, Manoharpura, Mathura.<br />\r\nOther Modes - Taxis, Auto rickshaws, Cycle Rickshaws and Car hire services are also available within the city.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center">1 - SHANKAR MITHAIWALA - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORI, SAMOSA, LASSI AND LAL PEDA)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center">2 - VISHRAM GHAT, IN CHATTA BAZAR OPP KANHAIYA CLOTH MARKET - (FAMOUS FOR PANI PURI AND CHAAT)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center">3 - BRIJWASI ROYAL MITHAIWALA, AT HOLI GATE, SHRI KRISHNA JANM BHOOMI ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR SWEETS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - ANNAPURNA KHAMAN &nbsp;DHOKLA HOUSE, IN CHATTA BAZAR - (FAMOUS FOR KAMAN DHOKLA AND POHA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '6,8,11,16,25'),
(116, 14, 31, 745, 'Maharashtra', 'INDIA', 'PUNE', 'warli-958606_1280.jpg', 'live-concert-388160_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">A thriving, vibrant metropolis, Pune is a centre of academics and business, with its mix of capitalism, spiritualism, ancient and modern. Pune was initially given pride of place by Shivaji and the ruling Peshwas, who made it their capital. What makes Pune more significant is that it is a place from where you can plan several exciting trips to hill-stations, forts, and places of pilgrimage, not to forget an adventurous package too. Popularly known as the &lsquo;Oxford of the East&rsquo;, Pune hosts a number of universities and colleges including one of India&rsquo;s oldest Universities that attract both Indian and International students.Pune is also be considered as a halting place for the Ashtavinayaka, and the Bhimashankar. Being a modern city, Pune offers a lot to culture and music buffs, food and fashion lovers. Discotheques and pubs are there. &#39;Rain dances&#39; and beauty pageants are held regularly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">i). Pimpri<br />\r\nPimpri is a suburb of Pune in the Pune Metropolitan Area in the state of Maharashtra. It is located to the North-West of Pune city and is well connected to the center of&nbsp;Pune city via the Old Pune-Mumbai Highway.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">ii). Chinchwad<br />\r\nChinchwad is a suburb in Pune Metro City in the state of Maharashtra, India. It consists of the twin towns of Pimpri and Chinchwad which are governed by a common municipal body. It is located in the North-West of Pune and is well connected to the center of the city via the Old Pune-Mumbai Highway.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Being one of the most popular destinations in India, tourists can easily find budgeted accommodation around the city. Pune offers a variety of accommodations from budget hotels to the most lavish properties.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>a). Bus Service: Both public and private transport are popular in Pune. Public buses within the city and its suburbs are operated by the Pune Mahanagar Parivahan Mahamandal Limited (PMPML). Maharashtra State Road Transport Corporation runs buses from its main stations to all major cities and towns in Maharashtra and Neighbouring States.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b).Railway: Local trains (EMUs) connect Pune to the industrial town of Pimpri-Chinchwad and the hill station of Lonavala, while at Pune Junction&nbsp;daily express trains connect to all other cities of the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c). Airport: Pune is well connected through domestic airlines with the entire country. The airport located at Lohgaon has recently acquired status of an international airport and is being used to carry domestic as well as international traffic.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d). Metro Rail Service: A mass transit system called Pune Metro has been proposed for the city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e). Other Modes: Local Taxis and Cab Services are the most popular modes of transportation within the city.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><br />\r\n<strong>1- YANA, IN GOLD ALDLABS, KALYANI NAGAR, IN FC ROAD, &amp; IN SHIVAJI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR SIZZLERS)<br />\r\n2- BEDEKAR, IN SHAGUN CHOWK - (FAMOUS FOR MISSAL)<br />\r\n3 - SHARVAREE, AT CORNER OF FERGUSON COLLAGE - (FAMOUS FOR MAHRASHTRIAN THALI)<br />\r\n4 - SHABREE, ON FC ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR MAHRASHTRIAN THALI)<br />\r\n5 - DURUVANKUR,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;AT HATHI GANPATI CHOWK, TILAK ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR MAHRASHTRIAN THALI)<br />\r\n6 - SUKANTA, IN DECCAN NEAR Z BRIDGE OFF JM ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR MAHRASHTRIAN THALI)<br />\r\n7 - SINGHAD FORT, IN SINGHAD - (FAMOUS FOR PITHAL BHAKRI)<br />\r\n8 - VAISHALI, AT SHIVAJI NAGAR, FC ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR SOUTH INDIAN CUSINE)<br />\r\n9 - ROOPALI, ON FC ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR SOUTH INDIAN CUSINE)<br />\r\n10 - WADESHWAR,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;AT THORIE BAJIRAO PESHWA ROAD, SADASHIVPETH - (FAMOUS FOR SOUTH INDIAN CUSINE)<br />\r\n11 - MARX-