(127, 14, 31, 745, 'Maharashtra', 'INDIA', 'SATARA', 'castle-857362_1920.jpg', 'castle-857362_19201.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Satara District is a district in the Maharashtra state of India, near the confluence of the river Krishna and river Venna other major towns include Wai, Karad, Koregaon, Koynanagar, Rahimatpur, Phaltan, Mahabaleshwar and Panchgani. The city derivied its name from the seven glorious hills surrounding it (Sat-Tara), &amp; is famous for its sweet kandi pedhe. The city was established in the 16th century and was the seat of Raja of Satara. The City has a unique statue of Shivaji standing near a canon at Powai Naka and also houses Kas plateau / Flower plateau which is now a World Natural Heritage site.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>The Accomodation facilty is good in the city ranging from budget to luxury hotels easily available all across the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Airport</strong> - The Nearest airport that serves the city in Pune Lohegaon Airport about 100 kms from Satara<br />\r\n<strong>Railway</strong> - The City is served by Satara Railway Station at Kshetra Mahuli, Satara.<br />\r\n<strong>Bus Stand</strong> - Intra State &amp; City Bus services are easily avilable in the city. Other private luxury buses are also operated and easily availbale in the city.<br />\r\n<strong>Other Modes</strong> - Autorickshaws, Taxis and other car hire services are also available easily all across the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - LATKAR BANDHU SWEET MART, LOCATED AT BHAVANI PERTH RAJPATH SATARA, SHANIWAR PETH, MALHAR PETH - (FAMOUS FOR KANDI PEDHA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - KABADI PAV BHAJI CENTER, LOCATED AT BHAVANI PERTH RAJPATH SATARA, POWAI NAKA - (FAMOUS FOR PAV BHAJI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - SHRIMANT PESHWAI BHEL, LOCATED AT KALYANI NAGAR, AJINKYA COLONY, SADAR BAZAR - (FAMOUS FOR BHEL AND PANI PURI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - ROHAN&#39;S CAFE, LOCATED AT RAJEBHOSALE HEIGHTS, SADAR BAZAR - (FAMOUS FOR PAV BHAJI AND COLD COFFEE)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n5 - SNOWDROP, LOCATED AT SNOWDROP FOOD JUNCTION ORCHID MALL, MAIN MARKET MAHABLESHWAR - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;SANDWICH)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - BLACK PEARL CAFE, LOCATED AT AJINKYA COLONY, POWAI NAKA - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN CHEESE MANCHURIAN)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(128, 14, 31, 745, 'Maharashtra', 'INDIA', 'AMRAVATI ', 'maracaibo-111078_1920.jpg', 'maracaibo-111078_19201.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Amravat literally means &#39;the city of immortals&#39;, Amravati from long had its place of honour in both legend and history &amp; is also known as &quot;Ambanagari&quot;, &nbsp;whiich is a district in the Indian state of Maharashtra &amp; is the 8th most populous metropolitan area in the state. &nbsp;It is said that Amravati is named for its ancient Ambadevi temple. &nbsp;The ancient proof of existence of Amravati can be derived from stone carved inscription on the base of marble statue of God Adinath (Jain God) Rhishabhnath. Udumbaravati was the ancient name of today&#39;s Amravati and was due to the presence of huge number of Audumber trees in the region.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">i) Achalpur - The place formerly known as Ellichpur and Illychpur, is a city and a municipal council in Amravati District. It is located 54 KM towards North from District head quarters Amravati. &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>To cater the visitors the district has got an array of hotels and resorts from big and luxury to small and affordable &amp; limited budget accomodation as well.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Airport</strong> - Amravati airport is located in Bolera about 16 kms from city but does not have scheduled commercial flight services as of yet. The other nearest Airport is Dr. Babasaheb Ambedkar International Airport in Nagpur, 136 Kms from the town Connecting flights to major Indian cities.<br />\r\n<strong>Railway Station</strong> - The city is served by Amravati railway station which is connected with Badnera Junction &nbsp;Nai Basti, Amravati and is well connected to the major cities of India.<br />\r\n<strong>Bus Service</strong>- Intra State and Intra City bus services are available from the bus stand at Maltekdi Road, Near Oosmaniya Masjid, Amravati. Other private buses are also available in city.<br />\r\n<strong>Other Modes</strong> - Auto rickshaws, taxis and other car hire services are also available iin the city.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - Khana Khajana Restaurant, Near Jakat Naka, Khana Khajana, Walgaon Road, Amravati HO - (fmous For Biryani)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">2 - Madhuram Munching Food, Opp: D Mart, Badnera Road, SAI Nagar - (Famous For Fast Food)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">3 - Picnic Food, Near Amravati HO - (Famous For Fast Food)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - Lords Family Garden Restaurant &amp; Bar, at MIDC, Old Bypass Road, Amravati HO - (Famous For Punjabi Cusine)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">5 - Taste Of South, Near Circuit House Camp - (Famous For South Indian Food)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">6 - Meridian Restaurant, C/O Sripad Continental Hotel, Opp IKI College, MDS Road - (Famous For Maharashtrain Cusine)</p>\r\n', ''),
(129, 14, 31, 745, 'Maharashtra', 'INDIA', 'SANGLI ', 'amazing-736882.jpg', 'amazing-7368821.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">SANGLI city is located in the Indian state of Maharashtra on the banks of river Krishna, nearly 400 kilometers southeast of Mumbai. The district of Sangli is a recent creation made as late as in 1949 &nbsp;by the merger of three cities Sangli, Miraj &amp; Kupwad. The district is well known for its turmeric trade, grapes and sugar factories because of this district is also referred as &#39;Turemeric City of India&#39; as from here turmeric is imported to all major countries of the world and &#39;Sugar Bowl&#39; as the district itself houses more than 30 sugar factories. Sangli-Miraj cities are also well known for healthcare due to presence of famous hospitals like Wanless hospital &amp; Kripamayee Mental hospital &amp; Sidhivinayak cancer hospital. Sangli has also emerged as a major education city in Maharashtra. Kundal is a pilgrimage centre for the Digambar Jains in Sangli District visited every year by thousands of Jains.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">i) Miraj - The city is the part of Sangli district founded in the early 10th century. The city is recognised for performance of Indian classical music &amp; for its medical services. The Pathwardhan family were the hereditary rulers of Miraj until independence.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">ii) Kupwad - It is town in th Miraj taluka of Sangli district located located about 9 KM towards East from District head quarters of Sangli, is an industrial area harbouring many foundries, spinning mills, chocolate factories, oil manufacturing, cold storage etc.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>The city is having good level of accomodation easily availbale across the city from 5 star suites to budget hotels.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Airport</strong> - Nearest airport from Sangli is the Pune Airport in Lohegaon about 220 kms from city.<br />\r\n<strong>Railway Station</strong> - The city is served by Sangli Railway Station at Vishrambag.<br />\r\n<strong>Bus Service</strong> - Intra State bus service is available from S.T bus stand at Dr Ambedkar Rd, Patrakar Nagar, Sangli operated by MSRTC. Other private luxury buses are also avialable.<br />\r\n<strong>Other Modes</strong> - Auto Rickshaws are available easily in the city other car hire services are also availble in the city.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - BALLEBALLE RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT OPPOSITE SANGLI - KOLHAPUR OCTROI CHECK POST - (FAMOUS FOR MAKKE KI ROTI AND SARSO KA SAAG)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - BURGER POINT, LOCATED AT PANDHARPUR ROAD, OTHONIAL COLONY, MIRAJ - (FAMOUS FOR BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - CAFE BROASTA, LOCATED AT OPPOSITE WALCHAND COLLEGE BACK GATE, MSEB ROAD, VISHRAMBAUG - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - SHRI GANESH NASHTA CENTER, LOCATED AT KUPWAD ROAD, VISHRAMBAG CHOWK - (FAMOUS FOR POHA AND PAVBHAJI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - LANJEKAR SWEET SHOP, LOCATED AT BALAJI CHOWK,KAPAD PETH, GANAPATI PETH - (FAMOUS FOR PEDA AND CHIVADA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - MANGAL MITHAI BHANDAR, LOCATED AT CITY HIGH SCHOOL ROAD, GAON BHAG - (FAMOUS FOR PEDA AND KALAKAND)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(131, 14, 31, 742, 'Karnataka', 'INDIA', 'BANGLORE', 'kempegowda-international-airport-245024_1280.jpg', 'kempegowda-international-airport-245024_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Banglore officialy known as Bengaluru is the capital of Karnataka and is the 3rd most populus city in India and is also sometimes referred to as Silicon Valley of India because of being India&#39;s leading IT (Information Technology) Sector . Banglore is known for its pleasant climate throughout the year, nightlife and greenspace.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Banglore has many options varrying from delux to budget easily available across the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Banglore Airport</strong> - Kempegowda International Airport is an international airport serving Bangalore and is located about 40 kilometres north of the city near the village of&nbsp;Devanahalli.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Railway Station </strong>- The Bangalore City railway station, officially known as Krantivira Sangolli Rayanna railway station, is the main railway station serving the city of Bangalore, Karnataka, India. It is located across the Kempegowda Bus Station and is well connected to all major cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Bus Service</strong> - Intra State Bus Service is available all the time from local bus stand. BMTC (banglore metropolitan transport corporation) is a government agency that runs public transport bus facility.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Other Modes</strong> - Auto, Taxis like Meru ola, Auto Rickshaws, and metro train are also avilavble in city.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n1 - V.V PURAM FOOD STREET - (FROM HOT &amp; SPICY MASALA DOSA TO SWEET &amp; SUBLIME DAL HOLIPE)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - CENTRAL TIFFIN ROOM, IN MALLESHWARAM, AT MARGOSA ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR SOUTH INDIAN FOOD)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\