(132, 14, 31, 752, 'Rajasthan', 'INDIA', 'JAIPUR', 'amber-653180_1920.jpg', 'amber-653180_19201.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Jaipur is also populary known as Pink City and &ldquo;Paris of India&rdquo; is the Capital of Indian State Rajasthan &amp; was founded on 18 November 1727 by Maharaja Jai Singh II, the ruler of Amer after whom the city is named.Here the past comes alive in magnificent forts and palaces, blushed pink, where once lived the maharajas. The bustling bazaars of Jaipur, famous for Rajasthani jewellery, fabric and shoes. This place was India&#39;s first planned city. With spectacular hilltops and stunning fortresses. World&rsquo;s First Elevated Road under Metro in Pink City Jaipur Rajasthan Jaipur will be the first city in the world to have an elevated track under Metro and for Rapid Transport system is proposed for the city. The city is known for its rich culture and tradition, magnificent art and artefacts, and brilliant past.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Being the &nbsp;famous tourist destination among Domestic and International tourists the city offers wide range of accomdation facility from heritage properites, Resorts, budget to luxury with all the modern ameneties easily avialable all across the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Airport - The city is served by Jaipur International Airport in Sanganer 13 km from jaipur.<br />\r\nRailway Station - The city is served by Jaipur Junction railway station &nbsp;is a railway station in Jaipur &amp; also serves as the headquarters of the North Western Railway zone of the Indian Railways.&nbsp;<br />\r\nBus Service - Intra State bus service &nbsp;is availbale form bus terminal Sindhi Camp close to the station. Other private luxry bus services are also avilable in the city.<br />\r\nOther Modes - Taxis, Auto rickshaws and Car hire services (like Ola, Uber etc.) are also available within the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n1- IN JAIPUR - [FAMOUS FOR DAL BAATI CHURAM (RAJASTHANI MEAL), MIRCHI BADA, GATTE KI SABZI]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - RAWAT SWEETS, AT LMB, JOHRI BAZAR - (FAMOUS FOR MAWA KACHORI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - GHEWAR, AT LMB, JOHRI BAZAR - (FAMOUS FOR GHEWAR)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - HANDI RESTAURANT, IN MI ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR RED MEAT)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n5- LAXMI MISHTHAN BHANDAR, AT LMB, JOHRI BAZAR, BEHIND HAWA MAHAL, AJMER ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR PYAZZ KI KACHORI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n6 - RAWAT SWEETS, NEAR POLOVICTORY CINEMA, RAILWAY STATION ROAD, SINDHI CAMP - (FAMOUS FOR PYAZZ KI KACHORI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n7 - PANDIT, OPPOSITE BIRLA TEMPLE, JAWAHAR CIRCLE - (FAMOUS FOR PAV BHAJI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n8 - SAHU, AT CHAURA RASTA - (FAMOUS FOR MASALA TEA)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">9 - MURLI, OUTSIDE, 264, TRIPOLIA BAZAR - (FAMOUS FOR PAAN)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n10 - KOTA RATAN, AT JAGDAMBA TOWER, SHOP NO. 23, AMARPALI CIRCLE, VAISHALI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n11 - RAMCHANDRA, TRIPOLIA BAZAR, BADI CHOPPAR - (FAMOUS FOR KULFI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n12 - ANU MOBILE PAAN, NEAR PANCHWATI CIRCLE, RAJAPARK - [FAMOUS FOR BEST PAAN (IN WORLD)]&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '');
