(133, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'INDORE', 'jain-temple-1084350_1920.jpg', 'jain-temple-1084350_19201.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">It is one of the most populour city of the state Madhya pradesh. Also known as Education hub of the State due to IIT &amp; IIM campuses in the city. The city is located about 190 km to the west of Bhopal. Indore is 9th largest city in India and 76th largest city in the world. The city situated on thde banks of the River Khan and River Sarawati. At the centre of the city there exists a small temple of Lord Indreshwar. Indore is also known for its historical monuments and its architectural glow. &nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Being the &nbsp;famous tourist destination among Domestic and International tourists the city offers wide range of accomdation facility from heritage properites, Resorts, budget to luxury with all the modern ameneties easily avialable all across the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Airport</strong> - The city is served by Devi Ahilyabai Holkar Airport about 8 km from city. Frequent flights are available for varios cities, the airport also serves as the major hub for International cargo in Madhya Pradesh.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Railway Station</strong> - The city is served by Indore Junction railway station. Indore railway division comes under Ratlam Division of the Western Railways of the Indian Rai.&nbsp;The city is also served by seven other small railway stations within the city.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Bus Service</strong> - Atal Indore city transport services ltd. is availbale for local transportation as City bus on 36 Routes and around 170 bus stops approx. Other Indore BRTS(iBUS) with AC and non-AC bus services are also avilable in the city.<br />\r\n<strong>Other Modes</strong> - Taxis, Auto rickshaws and Car hire services are also available within the city.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n1 - RAJHANS - (FAMOUS FOR DAL BAAFLA LADOO)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">2 - CHAPPAN DUKAN - (FAMOUS FOR POHA JALEBI)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">3 - GURUKRUPA RESTAURANT - (FAMOUS FOR KAJU CURRY)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - PICHORI DHABA - (FAMPUS FOR TANDOORI CHICKEN AND KEBABS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n5 - CHAWANI BAZZAR, RAJBADA &amp; SARAF MARKET, IN OLD MARKETS OF INDORE - (FAMOUS FOR SABUNDANA KHICHDI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n6 - OLD MARKET OF INDORE - (FAMOUS FOR MOONG DAL BHAJIYAS AND IMARTI)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">7 - VIJAY CHAAT HOUSE - (FAMOUS FOR KHOPRA PATTIES, KACHORI &amp; SHIKANJI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n8 - APNA SWEETS, AT OLD PALASIA, SAPNA SNGEETA, VIJAY NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR SWE ND SNACKS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n9 - MADHURAM SWEETS, AT CHAPPAN DUKAN - (FAMOUS FOR RASMALI AND GUPCHUP)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">10- MAROTHIYO PEDEWALA,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;AT MAROTHIYO BAZAR, OLD PALASIA, ANAND BAZAR - (FAMOUS FOR SWEETS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n11- NEEMA SWEETS, IN OLD PALSIA, SAKET - [FAMOUS FOR KULFI (SWEET DISH)]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n12- MATHURAWALA, AT CHAWANI, RNT MARG - (FAMOUS FOR MAKKHAN VADE)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n13- AGARWAL SWEETS, AT OLD PALESIA, CHAPPAN DUKAN - (FAMOUS FOR SOAN PAAPDI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n14- RASGULLEWALE, AT GEET BHAVAN - (FAMOUS FOR SWEETS)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(134, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'JABALPUR', 'india-698826.jpg', 'india-6988261.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">JABALPUR a city in madhya pradesh, it is one of the major cities in madhya pradesh. Formerly jabalpur was known as JUBBULPORE and the nickname given to the city is &quot;The Marble City&quot;. A gun carriage factory was established in Jabalpur in 1904. Jabalpur has been called the cultural capital of Madhya Pradesh by &#39;Vinayak Narhari Bhave&#39;. The city and surrounding area population&#39;s culture is related with agriculture. Clothing and fooding of people changes with the season and the harvest. The city is surrounded by low and rocky hills. Khandari and Pariyat are primary reservoirs in northeast of the city. Several lakes and water tanks also surrounds the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The city offers wide range of accomdation facility from Resorts, hotels budget to luxury with all the modern ameneties easily avialable all across the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Airport</strong> - The city is served by JABALPUR Airport also known as Dumna Airport about 20 km from city centre. The spice Jet, Air India and Ventura Airconnect sreves frequent flights for major cities across the Country. The Airport also serves the visitors to Kanha National Park, Bandhavgarh National Park, Pench National Park, Khajuraho and Bhedaghat.<br />\r\n<strong>Railway Station</strong> - The city is served by Jabalpur Junction railway station in Jabalpur. The city railway division comes under West Central Railway of the Indian Railways. Direct trains are available to metropolitian and other major ciies. Jabalpur station is the last stoppage for train no. 10001 &#39;Satpura Express&#39; formerly the no. was train no.1 of Indian Railway.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Bus Service</strong> - Various cities are connected by raod to Jabalpur. National Hihgway 12 to Jaipur originates in Jabalpur and NH-7 India&#39;s longest highway runs through the city. Bus services to various cities of UP, Chhatisgarh, Maharashtra and MP are directly available.<br />\r\n<strong>Other Modes</strong> - Taxis, Auto rickshaws and Car hire services are also available within the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 -The Ristorante Lounge, at Kingsway Cantt, Above Lee Wrangler Showroom, Citi&Ecirc;Bazar Building, Sadar Bazar - (Famous For Coffe And Snacks)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">2 - Punjabi Food Corner, at &nbsp;Civic Center (Near Samdariya Mall and Post Office), Napier Town - (Famous For Parathas, Biryani, butter chicken and special chicken Samosa)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">3 - Clock Tower Chinese Restaurant, at Omti Bridge SH 22,Madhya Pradesh State Highway 37A,Naya Mohalla - (Famous for Chinese Food)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">4 - Famous Khopra Pak (coconut based dessert, kind of thickened sweet milk)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">5 - Famous Khoye ki Jalebi, at local sweet stalls&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">6 - Baba Falahari Chat, at Sarafa bazar - (Famous for Snacks made out of fruits and vegetables in milk specially Bbab ki chaat)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">7- Jain Kulfi, at Garha Road - [Famous for Kulfi (desert)]</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">8 - Ramnath, at Sarafa Bazar - &nbsp;(Famous For Snacks)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">9 - Gupta Chat at Civic Centre - (Famous For Pani Puri)<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(135, 14, 31, 1662, 'Goa', 'INDIA', 'GOA', 'india-1121506.jpg', 'india-11215061.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Neatly tucked into the Western coast of India, Goa is the state associated most with touristy beaches, happening nightlife and over 300-year old Portuguese architecture. Goa is home to everything refreshing, zesty, exotic and colourful. So is its food. Goa provides a rich mix of Indian culture with Portuguese effect. Visibly different from the rest of the country, Goa has characteristic colourful houses, lush green fields and a soothing languidness in atmosphere. The charming villages of Goa are ideal for a laidback morning walk or an aimless evening stroll. North and South regions of the place are strikingly different - the former is a cultural hub with traditional eateries and markets, while the latter is a luxurious side of it with 5-star hotels, private beaches and a mix of white sand and clean blue water. Under the star-laden skies, each festivity becomes more alive. Goa greens and wildlife makes for a nature lover&#39;s ideal hotspot. Goa&rsquo;s biggest draw is undoubtedly its virtually uninterrupted string of golden-sand beaches. This shimmering strand of sand stretches along the Arabian Sea from the tip to the toe of the state, and each of the various beaches have developed their own personalities and reputations since the hippie days of the sixties.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">i). Panaji&nbsp;<br />\r\nPanaji is the capital of the Indian state of Goa and the headquarters of North Goa district. It lies on the banks of the Mandovi River estuary in the Tiswadi taluka. Panaji is the first city in India to be built on a planned grid system One of India&rsquo;s smallest and most relaxed state capitals, Panaji crowds around the peninsula overlooking the broad Mandovi River, where cruise boats and floating casinos ply the waters, casting neon reflections in the night. A glorious white washed church lords over the animated city centre, a broad leafy boulevard skirts around the river, and grand colonial buildings rub shoulders with arty boutiques, old-school bookshops, state-of-the-art malls and backstreet bars.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">ii). Margao<br />\r\nMargao is the second largest city by population, and the commercial and cultural capital of South Goa. It&rsquo;s a useful place for shopping, catching a local sporting event or simply enjoying the busy energy of big-city in small-town form. By road, Margao is located approximately 33 kilometres from the capital Panaji, and 27 kilometres from Vasco da Gama.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">iii). Mapusa<br />\r\nMapusa is a town in North Goa. It is situated 13 Kms. North of the capital Panaji. The town is the headquarters of Bardez Taluka. Mapusa is a small town clustered around the Mount Alto. Mapusa has remained a prominent market centre for many centuries. Mapusa is the largest town in northern Goa, and is most often visited for its busy Friday market, which attracts scores of buyers and sellers from neighbouring towns and villages, as well as a healthy intake of tourists from the northern beaches. Numerous charity organisations, including International Animal Rescue and El Shaddai are nearby in Assagao. It&rsquo;s a good place to pick up the usual range of embroidered bed sheets and the like, at prices far lower than in the beach resorts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">iv). Pilar<br />\r\nPilar is a village in Goa, some 10 Kms. from the state capital Panaji. It is on a hill top and has a panoramic view of the Arabian Sea and the mountains all around. The site of Pilar is superb, reached by a narrow winding road that threads its way up the hill from the plains below. Set on a hill high above the surrounding countryside, is Pilar Seminary, one of four theological colleges built by the Portuguese. At the bottom of the hill is the old Church of Our Lady of Pilar, which still contains the original statue brought from Spain, along with lots of tombstones of Portuguese nobility, the grave of the locally famed Father Agnelo, and some attractive paintings in an alcove at the rear of the chapel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">v). Vasco-De-Gama<br />\r\nVasco de Gama is a city in the state of Goa. It is named after the Portuguese explorer Vasco de Gama. It is the headquarters of the Mormugao taluka. The city lies on the western tip of the Mormugao peninsula, at the mouth of the Zuari River. This strategically important town was formerly among the busiest ports on India&#39;s west coast. It remains a key shipping centre, with container vessels and iron ore barges clogging the choppy river mouth, but holds nothing of interest for visitors, particularly since the completion of the Konkan Railway, when Goa&#39;s main railhead shifted from here to Margao. Originally Vasco de Gama was founded by Portuguese during their rule in Goa in the year 1543 and within the short period it was established as Western India&rsquo;s busiest ports of all. Today at Sada, you see just remnants of the ramparts, actually it was the fort built by Portuguese in the same century after establishing Vasco as Western India&rsquo;s Port to control smooth operation of shipping.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">vi). Mormugao<br />\r\nMormugao is a sub-district and a municipal council in South Goa district. It is Goa&rsquo;s main port. Mormugao was an important port for Portuguese ships. Mormugao is the main port facility of Goa located at the tip of a peninsula jutting out into the Arabian Sea. It&rsquo;s a 45 -minutes drive to Panjim. Close to Mormugao is the small town of Vasco da Gama. It serves as terminus for the railway line into Goa. The atmosphere is easygoing and the people are very friendly. In the oldest part of the town, the Portuguese heritage has survived remarkably well? There are narrow, winding streets, old houses with overhanging balconies and red&not; tiled roofs, whitewashed churches and numerous small bars and cafes &not; an atmosphere more reminiscent of the Mediterranean than of India. The ships are docked at Mormugao Port.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">vii). Chandor<br />\r\nThis is the village which was once the location of the capital of Chandrapur rulers which also boasts of a fort and a temple within its citadel. It is located 10 kms from the inland of Margao and has both the ancient and modern aspects to its history. The ancient Chandor was once a port of international repute and a great capital where trade and commerce flourished. Its geographical location is just perfect with the loop of the Kushavati River with another tributary of the Zuari to the west. One of the most important capitals of Chandragupta, the Mauryan Emperor, and filled with inscriptions by Bhoja kings dating back to the 3rd century, Chandor, once known as Chandrapur, has retained much of its heritage from before the Portuguese rule and 13th century temple raids. Located on the banks of river Kushavati, Chandor has been the site for excavations, with pottery dating back to 200 BC found here along with an old, ruined statue of Nandi, Lord Shiva&#39;s bull, from 7th century belonging to the era of Chandraditya in 1929. Most of these excavations are displayed at their site of discovery for the public to see. A major attraction of Chandor and a living testament to Portuguese heritage is the Bragangca House.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Goa has places available for all categories of travellers. Whether you&#39;re on a shoestring budget and want a cheap shack or you&#39;re on the splurging spree and want to have the luxurious 5 star stay, whether you want a rented apartment to have house parties or you want just a mid-budget hotel for a few days, Goa has it all.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Airport:</strong> - Goa International Airport, is a civil enclave at INS Hansa, a Naval airfield located at Dabolim near Vasco de Gama. The airport caters to scheduled domestic and international air services.<br />\r\n<strong>Road:</strong> - Goa&#39;s public transport largely consists of privately operated buses linking the major towns to rural areas.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Railways:</strong> - Goa has two rail lines-one run by the South Western Railway and the other by the Konkan Railway.<br />\r\n<strong>Sea:</strong> - The Mormugao harbour near the city of Vasco handles mineral ore, petroleum, coal, and international containers. Much of the shipments consist of minerals and ores from Goa&#39;s hinterland. Panjim, which is on the banks of the Mandovi, has a minor port, which used to handle passenger steamers between Goa and Mumbai<br />\r\n<strong>Other:</strong> - Rent a motorbike or a car since destinations in Goa are quite a distance. One can get various types of geared and un-geared bikes and can also hire a cab, with or without a chauffeur. One way could be more effective than the other based on how many people are travelling.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n1 - GOA - [FAMOUS BEBINCA (SWEET OF GOA)]</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">2 - GOA - [FAMOUS AMBOT TIK SOUR &amp; SPICY (DISH OF GOA)]</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">3 - GOA - [FAMOUS CRAB XEC XEC A (DELICIOUS CURRY)]</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">4 - GOA&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;- [FAMOUS FISH CURRY AND RICE (GOA CUSINE)]</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">5 - GOA - [FAMOUS CHICKEN CAFRCAL HOT AND SPICY CHICKEN (1 OF MOST FAMOUS DISH IN GOA)]</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">6 - GOA - [FAMOUS GOAN FENI (LOCAL ALCHOHOLIC DRINK)]</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">7 - GOA - [FAMOUS MUSHROOM &nbsp;XACUTI (HOT &amp; SPICY GOAN DISH)]</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">8 - GOA - [FAMOUS PORK VINDALOO (PREPEARED FROM PORK)]</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">9 - GOA - [FAMOUS SOROPTEL (PREPARED FORM PORK)]</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">10 - GOA - [FAMOUS DODOL (GOAN SWEET DISH)]<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(136, 14, 31, 751, 'Punjab', 'INDIA', 'CHANDIGARH', 'sukhna-lake-724004_1920.jpg', 'sukhna-lake-724004_19201.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Chandigarh is a city and a union territory in the northern part of India that serves as the capital of the states of Punjab andHaryana. As a union territory, the city is ruled directly by the Union Government and is not part of either state. Chandigarh is the best-planned city in India, with architecture which is world-renowned, and a quality of life, which is unparalleled. Serenity and a city are two diametrically opposite concepts, which however, get belied in the &#39;City Beautiful&#39;. Chandigarh is a rare epitome of modernization co-existing with nature&#39;s preservation. It is here that the trees and plants are as much a part of the construction plans as the buildings and the roads. The city of Chandigarh was one of the early planned cities in the post-independence India and is known internationally for its architecture and urban design. The master plan of the city was prepared by Swiss-French architect Le Corbusier, transformed from earlier plans created by the Polish architect Maciej Nowicki and the American planner Albert Mayer.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Chandigarh hotels are pricier than elsewhere. Apart from the bus station&rsquo;s Transit Lodge, which readily accepts foreigners, there are two genuine budget options that are clean (for the price) and well run, but they are sometimes reluctant to take foreign guests.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Airways</strong>: - The airport is 11 km from downtown. Taxis are available for Airport transfer. Indian Airlines, Jet Airways and Air Deccan connects Chandigarh with New Delhi the National Capital. Chandigarh Tourism has well maintained Tourist Information Centre at the Airport.<br />\r\n<strong>Railways</strong>: - Chandigarh is linked with New Delhi, the National Capital by Rail. The Chandigarh Railway Station is 8 Kms from the city centre in Sector 17. The twice daily Shatabdi, Jan Shatabdi and Himalayan Queen connects New Delhi and Chandigarh. Paschim Express connects the city to Mumbai, Sadbhavna to Lucknow, Kerala Sampark Kranti to Kerala and Chennai Express to Chennai.<br />\r\n<strong>Roadways</strong>: - Chandigarh is well connected by road and buses provide an important transport link. There are services from various states such as- Haryana, Punjab, Himachal, and Delhi. The Union Territory of Chandigarh is well served by an excellent network of roads. Buses of several State Road Transport Corporations connect Chandigarh with many cities and towns of neighbouring states. Buses may be air-conditioned, deluxe, semi-deluxe or ordinary. The Inter-State Bus Terminus is located in Sector 17.<br />\r\n<strong>Other Modes:</strong> - The city has an excellent bus service run by Chandigarh Transport Undertaking (CTU). It serves as the best means of local transport. For traveling short distances, Rickshaws are just apt. Also, one can avail the services of Auto rickshaws that usually ply to and from the ISBT. Hop on Hop off Tourist Coach is one of its first kind in the country and is a major tourist attraction in itself due to its open top roof. The well furnished double decker coach moves in circular route covering all the major tourist destinations in the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><br />\r\n1 - NIKE BAKER&#39;S, IN SEC 9 &amp; SEC 35 - (FAMOUS FOR BAKERY PRODUCTS)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center">2 - WHISTLING DUCK, IN SCO 10, BACK LANE, SEC 26 - (FAMOUS FOR VARIETY OF CUSINE)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - HOPS IN GRAINS, &nbsp;IN SCO 358, SEC 9, PANCH KULA - (FAMOUS FOR BEING FIRST MICROBREWERY IN CITY)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - VIRGIN COURTYARD, AT SCO 1 A, BACKSIDE, MADHYA MARG, SEC 7 - (FAMOUS FOR ITALIAN FEEL AND CUSINE)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n5 - BACKPACKER&#39;S CAFE, AT SEC 9 D &amp; ELANTE MALL - (FAMOUS FOR SANDWICHES AND BURGERS)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center">6 - MONICA&#39;S, AT SEC 8 &amp; SEC 35 - (FAMOUS FOR CAKES AND PASTRIES)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n7 - PAL DHABA (OLDEST DHABA IN CITY), at SCO 151 &amp; 152 &amp; SEC 28&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;- (FAMOUS FOR VARIETY OF DISHES)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center">8 - THE WILLOW CAFE, AT&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;SCO 1, SEC 10, - (FAMOUS FOR SNACKS AND COFFEE)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center">9 - RAM CHAT BHANDAR, AT SEC 34 C - (FAMOUS FOR CHAAT)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center">10 - BHOLEY DI HATTI, AT SEC 44 D - (FAMOUS FOR PURE VEG STREET FOOD)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center">11 - PARATHA CORNER, AT JANTA MARKET, 27 D SECTOR 27 - (FAMOUS FOR PARATHA)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center">12 - MATRU TIKKI WALA, AT SEC 19 C - (FAMOUS FOR TIKKI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n13 - KORNZ FACTORY, AT GROUND FLOR, PARAS DOWNTOWN SQUARE MALL, ZIRAKPUR - (FAMOUS FOR VARIETY OF DISHES)<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(137, 14, 31, 1654, 'Tamil Nadu', 'INDIA', 'PONDICHERRY', 'pondicherry-1061484_1920.jpg', 'pondicherry-1061484_19201.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Pondicherry, now known as Puducherry, is a town tucked away on the Eastern seaboard of India. Some great food, some fine wine, and a great adventure awaits here. Pondicherry is a great place to look around, take a walk by the sea and attend a cultural program. Enjoy a fine meal with a glass of wine, rent a bicycle and take a ride at the promenade, take a walk in the park. Hotels, restaurants and &lsquo;lifestyle&rsquo; shops sell a seductive vision of the French-subcontinental aesthetic, enhanced by Gallic creative types whose presence has in turn attracted Indian artists and designers. The older part is full of quiet, clean, shady cobbled streets, lined with bougainvillea-draped colonial-era townhouses numbered in an almost logical manner. The newer side of town is typically, hectically South Indian. Puducherry is split from north to south by a partially covered canal. . It is affectionately known as Pondy, and has been officially known by the alternative name Puducherry since 2006.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">If you are trying to figure out where to stay in Pondicherry, you have a wide variety of choices. The options span from luxury heritage hotels to beach resorts and simple guest houses. Whether you are traveling to Pondicherry on a budget or trying to make it an all-out extravagance, there are accommodations to suit your needs. Guest houses are a type of inexpensive hotel-like lodging. It is a system that allows the visitor to rent a house for a short period and live with a feel of staying at home away from your home. If you are on the kind of holiday on which you want to spend time at the beach, Pondicherry has a few beach resorts. They are a little outside the city, so private transportation would be recommended. They all have a semi-private beach, a swimming pool, some great rooms, and restaurant.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong>: - Nearest airport is situated at Chennai, located 135-km from the city.<br />\r\n<strong>By Rail</strong>: - Pondicherry is connected with a meter gauge link with Chennai via Villupuram by the Pondicherry Express which is 36 km. from the city.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>By Road:</strong> - Pondicherry has a good network of roads, which connects it with most of South India.<br />\r\n<strong>By Bus</strong>: - The Pondicherry Road Transport Corporationruns buses within the city. The Tamil Nadu State Transport Corporation operates Volvo air-conditioned services from Chennai to Pondicherry. There are daily bus services from several main stops from Chennai.<br />\r\n<strong>Other:</strong> - There is no better way to explore the Pondicherry than one with riding your own vehicle. You can rent your favorite two wheeler and travel around the city independently.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>PONDICHERRY IS ESPECIALLY FAMOUS FOR FRENCH CUSINE.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">1 - LB2 LOUNGE - [FAMOUS FOR SALAD NICOISE; TOUILLE (PREPARED WITH TOMATO, GARLIC, ONIONS &amp; OTHER VEGETEBLE HERBS) &amp; CREPES (SWEET OR SAVOURY, VERY THIN PAN CAKE)]</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">2 - NEW BANANA CAFE, AT BAKERS STREET - [FAMOUS FOR QUICHE (OPEN BAKED TART WITH EGG CUSTARD FILLING)]</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">3 - MAISON ROSE, AT BAKERS STREET - [FAMOUS FOR STEAK-FRITES (BEAF STICK WITH FRENCH FRIES) &amp; CROISSANT (RICH PASTRIES)]</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">4 - THE PROMENADE - [FAMOUS FOR COQ AU VIN (PREPARED WITH CHICKEN, WINE, MUSHROOM &amp; GARLIC)]</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">5 - HOTEL LE VIETNAM - (FAMOUS FOR VEETNAMESE CUSINE)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">6 - DON GIOVANNI, AT MISSION STREET - (FAMOUS FOR ITALIAN CUSINE)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">7 - HOTEL ZAFFRON, IN ANNA SAALA - (FAMOUS FOR MALLU ARABIAN CUSINE)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">8 - AUROVILLE BAKERY, AT DOUCEUR, KULIAPALAYAM MAIN ROAD, AUROVILLIE - (FAMOUS &nbsp;FOR BAKERY PRODUCTS)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">9 - CAFE XTASI, OPP VOC SCHOOL, MISSION STREET - (FAMOUS FOR VARIETY OF PASTAS AND SALADS)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">10 - TAN PIZZERIA, AT AUROVILLE MAIN ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR VARIETY OF PIZZA)</p>\r\n', ''),
(138, 14, 31, 270, 'Andaman And  Nicobar Island', 'INDIA', 'ANDAMAN AND NICOBAR ISLAND', 'thailand-1451382_1920.jpg', 'thailand-1451382_19201.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Andaman &amp; Nicobar Islands is a group of over 572 Islands, islets and rocks (36 of which are inhabited) in the Bay of Bengal, South-East of the Indian mainland. &nbsp;The Group of islands covering a total area of 8,073 sq kilometres, the Andaman and Nicobar Islands are a union territory of the Republic of India. Initially inhabited by multiple groups of indigenous tribes, the island was later used as a penal colony during the British occupation of India. Despite of the horrid reputation during the colonial period, the Andaman and Nicobar Islands this day are one of the most sought after tourist destination of India. The islands are famous for its serene, white sandy beaches characterized by sparkling blue waters. Tourist infrastructure development has been on the rise over the year, but the islands still remain virgin with untouched natural beauty and unexplored marine life. Foreign tourists require a permit to stay from the Indian immigration authorities. Foreign tourists are issued a 30-day permit to visit the Andaman Islands. However, they are not permitted to visit the Nicobar Islands. Foreign nationals can extend their stay by another 15 days.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Accommodation in Andaman and Nicobar Islands is not at all a problem as there are plenty of standard hotels and resorts with all sorts of amenities to present you the experience of a lifetime. There are luxury hotels, Premium hotels and also Budget hotels in the Andaman and Nicobar Islands. There are also private and government lodges at affordable rate.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air</strong>: - Port Blair is connected with Delhi, Chennai and Kolkata by air. Flights are certainly faster, more comfortable and therefore the preferred option.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>By Sea</strong>: - Regular passenger ship services are available to Port Blair from Chennai, Kolkata and Vishakhapatnam and back. There are three to four sailings every month from Kolkata and Chennai to Port Blair and vice-versa. There is one sailing from Vishakhapatnam in a month. The voyage takes about 50 to 60 hours and the ship normally berths at Port Blair for about two to four days.<br />\r\n<strong>Local Transport:</strong> - Taxis, autos, buses, minibuses are the mode of local transport in Port Blair and other tourist places. Two wheelers are available for hire in most of the places for sightseeing. In small islands like Havelock and Neil, cycles are advisable for exploring places of interest. In Port Blair, pre-paid cab service is available at Airport (Arrival Hall) and Mohanpura, Opp. Bus terminus to all important outer islands connected by Road. Bus services are operated by Private Operators and also Transport department from Port Blair Mohanpura Bus Terminus to various places. Andamans offers different modes of transport including sea plane which runs only in Andamans, ride in Makkruzz, local carrier Dunghi and other such forms of boats.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(139, 14, 31, 0, 'DADRA AND NAGAR HAVELI', 'INDIA', 'DADRA AND NAGAR HAVELI', 'forest-208517_1920.jpg', 'forest-208517_19201.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Dadra and Nagar Haveli is one among the seven union territories in India. It is located on the west coast and is composed of two different parts-Dadra and Nagar Haveli. Dadra lies surrounded by Gujarat whereas, Nagar Haveli shares borders with Maharashtra and Gujarat. It lies in the watershed areas of Daman-Ganga River. As it shares borders with both Gujarat and Maharashtra, many of the languages are spoken here. There are many tribes who inhabited some areas of Dadra and Nagar Haveli. These tribes have their own indigenous culture and are self-sufficient. Green forests, rivers, large waterfronts, waterfalls, the gentle gurgle of streams, the distant hills, a gorgeous kaleidoscope of flora and fauna indicate nature of Dadra and Nagar Haveli. Dadra and Nagar Haveli enjoy a pleasant climate from November to March. Even the summer temperature is not very high. Due to its proximity to the sea, the nights are pleasant.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Dadra &amp; Nagar Haveli and capital city Silvassa offer a wide range of accommodation, including star category hotels, rustic cottages, tent complexes, tourist complexes and budget hotels, overlooking waterfronts or in the midst of forests. Most of the hotels in Silvassa and throughout Dadra and Nagar Haveli have specialty restaurants with well stocked bars, a swimming pool, heath club, massage and discotheque facilities, childcare and children&rsquo;s recreational activities. Government accommodation facilities are also available there as per the Govt. rates &amp; charges.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong>: - Nearest airport is at Mumbai (180 Kms. from Silvassa) which is well connected with all major cities of India and abroad.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>By Rail:</strong> - The nearest Railway station is Vapi on Western Railway. All major Mail/Express trains are available at Vapi, including August Kranti Rajdhani, Shatabdi, Ahinsa, Karnavati etc.<br />\r\n<strong>By Road</strong>: - Dadra &amp; Nagar Haveli almost touches the National Highway 8 between Mumbai and Delhi. Silvassa is about 14 Kms. from Bhilad and 18 Kms. from Vapi.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - NEW PATEL FARSAN MART, LOCATED AT DARA MANCHERJI VAID MARG KILVANI NAKA, SILVASSA - (FAMOUS FOR KHAMAN IS A SNACK MADE FROM GRAM FLOUR, CHANA DAL AND SERVED WITH PUDINA (MINT LEAVES), CHILLI, GARLIC, TARAMIND, CORIANDER, OR CHUTNEY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - VALENTINO RESTRO, LOCATED AT &nbsp;GJ SH 185, SILVASSA - (FAMOUS FOR UTHAPPAM, MASALA DOSA AND CHEESE CAKE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - SILVASSA CHINA TOWN, LOCATED AT &nbsp;NAROLI ROAD, AT JULIATE.C &amp; SON&#39;S AVENUE, ATHAL - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;FRIED RICE)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - MARUTI DOSA HOUSE SILVASSA, LOCATED AT SILVASSA - (FAMOUS FOR CHEESE DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - SHREEJI FAST FOOD AND RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT &nbsp;SILVASSA - BHILAD ROAD, NAROLI - (FAMOUS FOR PAV BHAJI)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(140, 14, 31, 1828, 'DAMAN AND DIU', 'INDIA', 'DAMAN AND DIU', 'cross-631002_1920.jpg', 'cross-631002_19201.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Daman &amp; Diu, the second smallest union territory is situated on the west coast of India. These twin islands were under the control of the Portuguese for a period of 450 years. The massive forts, magnificent cathedrals, and other impressive monuments of Daman &amp; Diu exude the subtle old world charm of its colonial era. Daman &amp; Diu is renowned for its natural splendour. The white sandy secluded beaches are quite inviting and offer many opportunities for water sports. Owing to its favourable climate, scenic location, and serene surroundings, Daman &amp; Diu is the most popular weekend gateway for nature lovers and adventure enthusiasts. Daman &amp; Diu are the sea side locations near Gujrat in Arabian Sea. Tourist attractions in Daman &amp; Diu are comprised of picturesque sun-bathed beaches, colonial forts and renowned churches. Besides this there is a rich heritage and culture of Daman &amp; Diu which offers very lively festive days and bustling nightlife, another tourist attraction in Daman &amp; Diu. Daman &amp; Diu have a mix of natural and manmade attractions. The Major Tourism Drivers and attractions in Daman can be categorised two heads: Heritage Attractions and Waterfront Attractions. In addition to these there are religious attractions and manmade attractions too like Water Park, Gardens etc. The major tourism drivers and attractions in Diu can be categorised two heads: Beach Attractions and Heritage Attractions. There are also other attractions like religious attractions, Caves etc.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Daman and Diu offers various kinds of hotels from star category to budget ones that offer comfortable rooms with basic amenities to its guests. Various hotels offer facilities and services keeping the comfort and requirement of the budget travellers. The availability of multiple budget hotels in Daman has made it easier and convenient for travellers to extend their stay without worrying about their budget.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong>: - Mumbai, the nearest domestic and international airport to Daman and Diu, is located at a distance of 193 Kms. All major airlines operate regular number of flights to and from Mumbai. One can also board flights to Diu from Porbandar and Mumbai. Another way to reach Daman and Diu is to reach Bhavnagar or Porbandar by flight and then take the motorable road to your final destination.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>By Train:</strong> - Vapi railway station is the nearest located railway station to Daman is only 12 Kms. away while the Delwada railway station is closely located to Diu. Ahmedabad and Mumbai are the two railway station of the western railways which are placed very close to Daman.<br />\r\n<strong>By Road:</strong> - Daman and Diu are also well connected to the other parts of India by an excellent road network. The National Highway No. 8 is used to connect Daman by the motorable road with Ahmedabad , Vadodara and Mumbai etc.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - AAHAR FAST FOOD, LOCATED AT NEAR HOTEL SOVEREIGN - (FAMOUS FOR SOUTH INDIAN FOOD, SANDWICHES AND CHEESE PIZZA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - TAWAKKAL RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT KHARIWAD - (FAMOUS FOR ROASTED CHICKEN AND CHICKEN PULAO)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - TASTY FAST FOOD &amp; RESTAURANT, LOCATED IN DIU - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA, ICE CREAM AND PASTRIES)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - FRIENDS BAKERY, LOCATED AT DUNETHA - (FAMOUS FOR CAKES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - AAHAR SNACKS PARLOUR, LOCATED AT &nbsp;MAIN ROAD, OPPOSITE BIBLOSS MARKET, NANI, DILIP NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR SANDWICH AND BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - JYOTI RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT &nbsp;DILIP NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR CHHOLE BHATURE AND ALOO PARATHA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - DAMAN AND DIU - (FAMOUS FOR COZIDO IS A DISH MADE FROM MEAT AND VEGETABLES)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(141, 14, 31, 743, 'Kerala', 'INDIA', 'LAKSHADWEEP', 'beach-1163966_1920.jpg', 'beach-1163966_19201.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Lakshadweep is a Union Territory and is governed by the Union Government of India. Literally meaning a &#39;hundred thousand islands&#39;, Lakshadweep has few of the most beautiful and exotic islands and beaches of India. The smallest Union Territory of India, Lakshadweep is a group of beautiful islands, located some 400 Kms. off India&#39;s west coast into the Arabian Sea. However there are only 36 islands having a total area of 32 sq. kilometres. It&rsquo;s made up of 12 atolls, 3 reefs and 5 submerged banks. Ten Islands are inhabited. Perhaps the charm of Lakshadweep islands lies in their remoteness. Far off the beaten track, they attract no hordes of merry markers to their shores. Or perhaps it is the beauty of the islands densely covered with coconut palms, and threaded by an unbroken line of creamy sand; each island serenely set in a sea whose waters range from palest aquamarine and turquoise to deepest sapphire and lapis lazuli. Yet again, may be the unique charm of Lakshadweep lies in the fact that each island, a tiny principality in itself, has existed from time immemorial, with little influence from the outside world. With fishing and coir production the main sources of income, local life on the islands remains highly traditional, and a caste system divides the islanders between Koya, Malmi and Melachers. The real attraction of the islands lies under the water: the 4200 sq km of pristine archipelago lagoons, unspoiled coral reefs and warm waters are a magnet for flipper-toting travellers and divers alike. According to the current Alcohol Laws of India, alcoholic beverage consumption is not permitted in the Lakshadweep Archipelago except on Bangaram Island. Tourists need a permit to visit the islands; foreign nationals are not permitted to visit certain islands.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Lakshadweep offers a wide range of accommodation from tourist huts to budget hotels and from 5-star holes and home stays to government guest houses.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Air:</strong> - Agatti Aerodrome on Agatti Island is the only airport in Lakshadweep. Air India Regional, a subsidiary of the state-owned carrier, serves Agatti and flies to Kochi on the mainland.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Other</strong>: - Lakshadweep is group of islands and to travel from one to another one can either use the ferry system or hire a Pawan Hans helicopter services. Several ships are also available from Kochi.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - CAFE DE SAINA, LOCATED AT KAVARATTI - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;TANDOORI ROTI(CHAPPAATI) AND FISH CURRY, FRIED RICE ,NOODLES SOUPS AND CHICKEN SANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - LAKSHADWEEP - (FAMOUS FOR COCONUT BONDAS IS A SNACK MADE FROM COCONUT, BOILED AND MASHED POTATOES, GREEN CHILIES, MUSTARD SEEDS, CUMIN SEEDS)&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(142, 14, 31, 734, 'Bihar', 'INDIA', 'PATNA', 'roof-1559814_1920.jpg', 'roof-1559814_19201.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Bihar&rsquo;s busy capital sprawls out over the south bank of the Ganges, just east of the river&rsquo;s confluence with three major tributaries. There&rsquo;s nothing for the traveller along the river itself, and Patna only has a handful of worthwhile sights. Otherwise, it&rsquo;s a chaotic, congested city that&#39;s used mostly as a transport hub, or as a base for day trips to sights in northern Bihar. Patna stretches along the southern bank of the Ganges for about 15 Kms. The 5.7 Kms. long Mahatma Gandhi Setu, one of the longest river bridges in the world, connects Patna with Northern Bihar. Patna is the capital of Bihar state. It is located on the south bank of the river Ganga. It is well connected by railway and road. It is mainly an administrative and educational centre of Bihar. It has however a few ancient sacred places as also places of tourist interest. Rice is the main crop of the district. It accounts for more than one third gross area sown.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Patna offers a mixed variety of hotels for accommodation. Being the capital and a starting place for the Buddhist Circuit and the Jainism Circuit, the city has developed good facilities to offer to the guests. Most of the hotels provide travel arrangement for touring the nearby places. One can stay in western style air-conditioned and non-air-conditioned hotels. There are also a number of moderately priced hotels around the railway station and the airlines office. Tourists can also stay at the Tourist Bungalow of Bihar State Tourism Development Corporation.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road:</strong> - Patna is well connected with all the major cities of Bihar and the rest of India. An excellent road network links Patna to major cities and tourist destinations within Bihar. Intra-city road transportation is also good in Patna.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>By Air:</strong> - Patna has regular flights from different cities of India. Cities like Delhi, Mumbai, Chennai, and Kolkata are linked with Patna with regular flights. Several Airlines including Air India and Jet Airways serve the city with regular flights.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>By Rail:</strong> - Patna is a major junction of Indian railway and is linked with all the major and minor cities of India via railway network. Patna has many regular trains from Delhi, Mumbai, Kolkata, Guwahati, Bangalore and Chennai.<br />\r\n<strong>Local Transport:</strong> - The local transport of Patna is easily available during the day time, however during late night there may be problem. There are plenty of options to move around the city and visit its various places at an affordable price. The fare is relatively low. The various modes of transportation in the city are Auto rickshaws, Cycle rickshaws, Cabs etc.<br />\r\n<strong>Bus Services</strong>: - City buses ply between the important destinations. These are mid size buses having seats for 25-30 people.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>BELOW MENTIONED ARE THE TRADITIONAL DISHES OF PATNA AND MUST TO BE TASTED BY EVERY VISITOR</strong><br />\r\n1 - LITTI CHOKHA (TRADITIONAL DISH OF BIHAR)<br />\r\n2 - DALL PITHA (PREPARED BY RICE FLOUR, LENTILLS AND GHEE)<br />\r\n3 - KHAJA (SWEET DISH OF BIHAR)<br />\r\n4 - GAYA SPECAIL TILKUT (SWEET DISH)<br />\r\n5 - THEKUA ((TRADITIONAL DISH, ALSO AS MAIN PRASAD IN CHATT)<br />\r\n6 - BALUSHAHI (POPULAR SWEET DISH OF BIHAR)<br />\r\n7 - PARWAL KI MITHAI (SWEET DISH OF BIHAR)<br />\r\n8 - ANARSA (SWEET DISH)<br />\r\n9 - SATTU SHARBAT (POPULAR DRINK OF BIHAR DURING SUMMERS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(143, 14, 31, 1658, 'Odisha', 'INDIA', 'BHUBANESHWAR', 'wat-phra-1470478_1920.jpg', 'wat-phra-1470478_19201.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Known as &ldquo;The City of Temples&rdquo;, Bhubaneshwar is one of the most culturally effervescent cities in India. The state capital of Odisha is a sprawling metropolis that very ably preserves the balance between upholding olden values and cultural heritage on one hand and being able to conform to changing modern times on the other. Bhubaneswar is home to some of the finest temples including the Lingaraja Temple and Mukteswar Temple. Nearby places of interest include the sacred pilgrimage town of Puri and the quiet ocean-side village of Gopalpur-on-Sea. Other tourist attractions include the State Museum, Bindu Sarovara and Nandan Kanan. The capital of Orissa, Bhubaneswar is scenic, lively, green and clean, with a rich cultural life. Known for its temples the city is a major centre of attraction for tourist from far and wide. It is probably the only city that enables an authentic over view of the stages of development of Hindu temple architecture. It is the place where temple building activities of Odishan style flowered from its very inception to its fullest culmination extending over a period of one thousand years. Today Bhubaneswar is an embodiment of its dashing modernity and glorious past. A favourite excursion from Bhubaneswar is a drive to the pilgrimage town of Puri, also known for its beaches. Bhubaneswar today is a model of liveability evident by the city&rsquo;s stable growth rate in the recent decades. It is one of the few cities that have been able to successfully capitalize upon its assets- be it the tangible and intangible heritage or its strategic location- into economic drivers that have shaped the city&rsquo;s growth in the recent decades.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">A wide array of hotels in the city boasts of offering just the right kind of accommodation in budget. Well equipped rooms well equipped with all the needs of the modern day sensitive traveller are available at various luxury Bhubaneshwar hotels to make the stay comfortable. Some luxury resorts set up in the exclusive setting of a beach offers world class facilities. All the comforts of a five star are also available even on a pilgrimage destination of Bhubaneshwar. Some of these hotels even arrange for flight bookings and car rentals for journey ahead and local sightseeing. Economic deals on much unbelievable prices are offered to the tourists by various budget hotels in Bhubaneshwar. These budget hotels also provide the best of services throughout stay and make the vacations even more memorable.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Air:</strong> - The Biju Patnaik Airport at Bhubaneswar provides daily connections to Kolkata and Delhi. Indian, Jet Airways, Air Sahara and Air Deccan are the domestic airlines also flying to Chennai, Visakhapatnam, Mumbai and Hyderabad. The airport is 4 Kms. from the town centre.<br />\r\n<strong>Rail:</strong> - Superfast trains connect Bhubaneswar to major cities of India. A major railhead on the East Coast (E Co) Railway, it has fast and super fast train links to all major cities directly.<br />\r\n<strong>Bus/Road:</strong> - Bhubaneswar is well linked to the rest of India by the national highways. The New Bus Stand in Bhubaneswar is on NH No. 5, at Baramunda, about 6 Kms. from town centre.<br />\r\n<strong>Local Transport:</strong> - There are prepaid taxis and auto rickshaws as local modes of transport. OTDC offers car-and-driver services for tours around the area. Private cab services are also available to move around the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n1 - BHUBANESHWAR - [FAMOUS MACHHA GHANTA(PREPARED FROM FISH PIECES, BENGAL GRAM. ONION, EGG PLANT, POTATO); CRAB KALIA (FRESH COOKED CRABS ALONG WITH &nbsp;POTATOES, GINGER AND ONIONS; CHUDA POHA; CHUNGDI MALAI (PREPARED WITH PRAWN AND CREAM); MURG SAAGWALA (CHICKEN PIECES COOKED WITH SPINACH GRAVY ALONG WITH GREEN MANGO); BHENDI BHAJA (IS SILTED LADYFINGER STUFFED WITH MIXTURE OF SPICES ABD GARLIC PASTE); CHENA JALEBI (PREPARED BY FRESH COTTAGE CHESE); MALPUA (SWTTENED WHEAT FLOUR BATTER, DEEP FRIED)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">2 - MAY FAIR, AT LAGOON, JAYDEV VIHAR - (FAMOUS FOR SNAX)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">3 - FOOD DAY, NEAR DURGA MANDIR, SHAHID NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR BIRYANI)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">4 - GUPTA&#39;S SWEETS &amp; CHATS, AT CUTTACK ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR SWEETS)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">5 - FOOD BOX, AT BMC, NEAR RD COLLAGE, SHAHID NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR CHINESE CUSINE)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">6 - CHAAT LOUNGE, AT FANCY MARKET, SHAHID NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR SNACKS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '');
