(144, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'BHOPAL', 'sunset-14782.jpg', 'sunset-147821.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Bhopal, the capital of Madhya Pradesh, is a fascinating amalgam of scenic beauty, old historic city and modern urban planning. Split by a pair of lakes, Bhopal is two cities within a city. Towards the North the old city, a fascinating area of mosques, serpentine alleys, chowks, crowds, exotic havelis and crowded bazaars. South of the two lakes is the new Bhopal. Modern, with wide roads, upmarket shopping complexes, and plush hotels and restaurants nestled comfortably in the area and Shamla Hills, which overlook the lakes and the old city beyond. The central district is known as New Market. Both Bhopal&rsquo;s enamour you in their own way and vie to bring out the child within you. The two lakes of Bhopal still dominate the city, and are indeed its nucleus. Bordered along the shores stand silent sentinels that testify to the growth of the city. Bhopal today presents a multi-faceted profile; the old city with its marketplaces and fine old mosques and palaces still bears the aristocratic imprint of its former rulers, among them the succession of powerful Begums who ruled Bhopal from 1819 to 1926. &nbsp;Equally impressive is the new city with its verdant, exquisitely laid out parks and gardens, broad avenues and streamlined modern edifices. &nbsp;It is greener and cleaner than most cities in the country.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There is a fairly wide variety of places to stay and hotel accommodation to choose from - deluxe, standard and budget, depending on what you want to spend. Bhopal offers the most luxurious palace hotels and classic heritage hotels dating back to the late 19th century. The older city of Bhopal has the Jehan Numa Palace Hotel and Noor us Sabah hotel where you can savour the tastes of Mughal aristocracy. The new Bhopal area has hotels which are more suited for the business traveler. The Hotel Lake View run by the Ashoka group The Residency, Nisarga are good places to consider.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Reaching by Air</strong>: - Bhopal airport, about 13 Kms. Northwest of the city centre, is well connected to cities like Delhi, Mumbai, Hyderabad, Pune and Raipur. Taxis are available from the airport to reach the city centre.<br />\r\n<strong>Reaching by Rail:</strong> - Bhopal is on the Delhi-Chennai main line. Major trains going from Mumbai to Delhi via Itarsi and Jhansi also go through Bhopal.<br />\r\n<strong>Reaching by Road:</strong> - Regular state run and private bus services connect Bhopal with Indore, Mandu, Ujjain, Khajuraho, Pachmarhi, Gwalior, Sanchi, Jabalpur and Shivpuri.<br />\r\n<strong>Local Transport:</strong> - Radio Taxi and auto-rickshaws are another major means of transport. In some parts in the old as well as new city, the new Tata Magic Vans are running successfully and have replaced the older and bigger diesel Rickshaws-known as &quot;Bhat&quot;.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - BHOPAL - {LOCATED AT &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;FAMOUS FOR BAFLA IS A WHEAT CAKE MADE FROM REFINED FLOUR OR MAIDA AND IS DUNKED WITH GHEE ; &nbsp;ROGHAN JOSH IS A DISH MADE FROM LAMB MEAT, ONIONS, SHALLOT, SPICES LIKE CLOVES, CARDAMOM, CINNAMON, CHILLIES AND SERVED WITH TANDOORI ROTI OR RUMALI ROTI ; &nbsp;BIRYANI PILAF IS A DISH THAT IS PREPARED WITH BASMATI RICE ALONG WITH MANY TYPES OF SPICES, MEAT, VEGETABLES, CREAM AND GHEE ; KEEMA PULAV IS A NON-VEGETARIAN DISH MADE FROM LAMB MEAT COOKED WITH BASMATI RICE ALONG WITH SPICES AND HERBS ; ACHAR GOSHT IS A MEAT DISH PREPARED FROM CHICKEN COOKED WITH PICKLE SPICES}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - NERBADA SWEETS &amp; RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT ROYAL MARKET - (FAMOUS FOR CHAAT, PANI PURI AND SANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - PARATHA HOUSE &amp; RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT OPPOSITE ST MONTFORT SCHOOL, RAISEN ROAD, PATEL NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR ALOO PARATHA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - VISHNU FAST FOOD, LOCATED AT BDA COMPLEX, LINK ROAD, SHIVAJI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR PANEER KULCHA AND PASTA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - MAYURIS FOOD PLANET, LOCATED AT 42, AMAITAS PHASE - 1, KOLAR ROAD, MANBHAWAN, CHUNA BHATTI - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;BUTTER PANEER MASALA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - FOOD CRAFT, LOCATED AT C-8, KOLAR ROAD, MANDAKINI SOCIETY - (FAMOUS FOR CHOLA BHATURA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - RAJU BHAI AMAR HOTEL, LOCATED AT OBEDULLA GANJ RD, NEAR HOTEL KAMLA, M P NAGAR, ZONE-II, MAHARANA PRATAP NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN CURRY)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n8 - ROLLS MANIA GULMOHAR, LOCATED AT GREEN CITY MALL, KRISHNA VIHAR - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN ROLL)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>9 - RAJ SWEETS &amp; RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT KAMLA NAGAR, KOTRA SULTANABAD - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSAS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>10 - SWEET POSSE, &nbsp;LOCATED AT OPPOSITE HAKEEM&#39;S, HOSHANGABAD ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR PAV BHAJI, PANEER MASALA WITH LACCHA PARATHA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>11 - VEERA DI HATTI, LOCATED AT METRO PLAZA, BITTAN MARKET, NEAR DUSSERA GROUND, ARORA COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR BUTTER CHICKEN, CHICKEN TIKKA AND MUTTON KEBAB)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>12 - BETWEEN 2 BREADS, LOCATED AT MAHENDRA COMPLEX, M.P. NAGAR, ZONE 1 NEAR CITI BANK - (FAMOUS FOR SANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>13 - BRIJWASI SWEETS, LOCATED AT SERVICE ROAD, ZONE-I, MAHARANA PRATAP NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR PANI PURI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n14 - MANOHAR&#39;S KHATTA MEETHA, LOCATED AT NEW MARKET, STT NAGAR, TT NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR PANI PURI, PAV BHAJI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>15 - CHANCHAL SWEET HOUSE, LOCATED AT BLOCK A, HEMU KALANI, BAIRAGARH - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSAS, KACHORI, CHHOLE-TIKIYA, AND CHHOLE-BHATOORE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>16 - KWALITY SWEETS, LOCATED AT RAISEN ROAD, PIPLANI, SONAGIRI - (FAMOUS FOR PANEER TIKKA PATTIES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>17 - MAMA SWEETS AND RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT &nbsp;INFRONT OF KASTURBA HOSPITAL, N-2, HABIB GANJ - {FAMOUS FOR PANEER PATTIES, SAMOSA AND TEA(CHAI)}</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(145, 14, 31, 1654, 'Tamil Nadu', 'INDIA', 'CHENNAI', 'india-193022_1280.jpg', 'india-193022_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Chennai or Madras as it was called before, on the Coromandel Coast, is the capital city of Tamil Nadu, a State of the Indian Sub continent. It is a major industrial, commercial, cultural, economic and educational centre of the Southern India. Chennai City is the sixth largest populated in Indian cities. It is known as the &quot;Detroit of India&quot; because many automobile industries are located here. Beautiful Beaches, One day leisure outlets, Modern Sea Port and Airport, Long and beautiful Highways, Convenient multi-Transport system, Theme parks, Industrial cities, Hi-Tech software silicon valley parks, Sophisticated Multi Speciality Hospitals, World Class Universities, High Rise Business and Residential complexes are the present days outlook of the great Chennai, most sought after by the people of all walks of life from all parts of the world. History is etched in every corner of the city of Chennai. While the city was the seat of power for many South Indian kingdoms through the ages, the documented history of the city began in the colonial times when the British stepped on the shores of Chennai and settled with the establishment of Fort St. George in1644. Chennai played a theatre of battle between the British, and the French colonial forces and also the kingdom of Mysore.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Being one of the major cities in the country, Chennai offers several accommodation options to suit every budget. Most of the mid-range and budget hotels are situated in Mylapore, T-Nagar and Egmore. Most of the five-star hotels are situated in Anna Salai.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Chennai has both domestic and international airports. Chennai is well connected to several Indian cities like Mumbai, Delhi, Bengaluru, Ahmadabad, Guwahati, Hyderabad, Kolkata, Kochi, Port Blair, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Chennai Central, Egmore and Tambaram are the three railway stations in Chennai. Chennai is well connected to most major parts of the country like Mumbai, Delhi, Bengaluru, Goa, Ahmadabad, Bhubaneswar, Bilaspur, Chandigarh, Coimbatore, Dehradun, Ernakulam, Gaya, Gorakhpur, Kolkata, Hyderabad, Indore, Jaipur, Jammu, Jodhpur, Kanyakumari, Mangalore, Madurai, Patna, Pondicherry, Jamshedpur, Thiruvananthapuram, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Chennai is well connected by 5 highways to all the major cities as well as states. Chennai bus station is considered as Asia&#39;s largest bus station. It has a great frequency of buses to and from Chennai. This connectivity makes Chennai a place most visited by tourists.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Chennai Metro Rail </strong>- Chennai Metro Rail is a new part of underground rapid transit system for moving around the city much easier. Line 1 goes from the airport to Teynampet, Thousand Lights, Central train station, the High Court and Washermanpet in northern Chennai, running beneath Anna Salai for several kilometres. Line 2 goes from Central train station west to Egmore and the CMBT then south to St Thomas Mount.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Other Modes </strong>- Taxis and rickshaws are easily available from the station to reach anywhere in the city. There are pre-paid auto rickshaw booths outside the CMBT and Central station, and 24-hour pre-paid stands with fare charts outside the north and south exits of Egmore station. Both airport terminals have pre-paid taxi kiosks. There&#39;s a pre-paid taxi stand outside the south side of Egmore station.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - CHENNAI - [FAMOUS FOR BAJJ (MOLGA BAJJI); ADAI (TASTY MIXTURE OF INGRIDENTS BEST EATEN WITH JAGGERY); PONGAL (MADE BOTH SPICY AND SWEET); CHETTINAD CHICKEN (LOADED WITH VARIETY OF MASALAS; FISH CURRY; PANNER SODA (SOFT DRINK); ROSE MILK (SOFT DRINK)]&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - RANGOLI GHAT, IN NUNGAMBAKKAM HIGH ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR PAN KULFI &amp; PANI PURI)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">3 - OSB HOT CHAAT, IN WEST MAMBALAM - (FAMOUS FOR DAHI PURI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - SWAMINATH CAFE - (FAMOUS FOR ONION UTTAPAM)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n5 - ATHO MAN - [FAMOUS FOR ATHO&#39;S (I.E VERSION OF NOODLES PREPARED FROM BURMESE CUSINE)]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n6 - ONLY VADA, IN KK NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR VADAS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n7 - MURUGAN IDLY SHOP, IN TILAK NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR HOT SAMBHAR AND DELICATE IDLIS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n8 - ANDHIKAKKADI (VATHAL KUZHAMBU) - (FAMOUS FOR THICK SPICY AND TANG GRAVY BASE DISH MADE WITH DRIED VEGETABLES)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n9 - KANNADASAN MESS, AT NATESAN PARK ROAD, TILAK NAGAR - [FAMOUS FOR KOTHU PAROTTAS (I.E LAYERED FLAT BREAD FILLED WITH DIFFERENT FILLINGS)]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n10 - HOTEL SARAVANA BHEWAN - [FAMOUS FOR IDDIYAPAM (I.E STRING HOPPERS BASICALLY STEMED NOODLES MADE FROM RICE FLOUR)]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n11 - SANGEETHA VEG RESTAURANT - (FAMOUS FOR CRISPY DOSA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n12 - THE KALAN SHOP, IN AROT ROAD - [FAMOUS FOR KALAN (ROAD SIDE SNACK MADE OF MUSHROOM)]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n13 - MADRAS COFFEE SHOP - (FAMOUS FOR FILTER COFFEE)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n14 - ROYAL SANDWICH SHOP - (FAMOUS FOR QUIRKY SANDWICHES I.E OF MAGGI LAYS, WHITE CHOCLATE SANDWICHES)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n15 - RASAM RICE - [FAMOUS FOR RASAM (RASAM IS BROTH GENRALLY MIXED WITH RICE)]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n16 - KUZHI PANIYARAM - [FAMOUS FOR DEEP FRIED IDLY BATTER]&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(146, 14, 31, 738, 'gujarat', 'INDIA', 'AHMEDABAD', 'sundial-590304_1920.jpg', 'sundial-590304_19201.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Located on the banks of river Sabarmati, Ahmedabad is the largest city in the whole state of Gujarat. From the year 1960 to 1970, it served as the capital city of Gujarat. However, later on, the capital was shifted to the Gandjhinagar city. It was founded in the year 1411 by Sultan Ahmed Shah. Ahmedabad is the hub of trade and commerce in Gujarat. The commercial importance of Ahmedabad makes the city an important travel destination in India. Besides being home to a number of important industries, Ahmedabad also has a number of majestic monuments, which remind us of the great historical and cultural past of the city. Ahmedabad was incorporated into the Bombay Presidency during the British rule but remained the most important city in the Gujarat region. Over a period of time, Ahmedabad established itself as the home of textile industry and earned the nickname of &quot;the Manchester of the East.&quot; A rising centre of higher education, information technology and scientific industries, Ahmedabad continues to remain one of the important cultural and commercial centres of western India. &nbsp;Although Ahmedabad is a bustling metropolitan with reputed institutes and a rapidly growing economy, it is also deeply rooted in tradition. The city is known for its association with Mahatma Gandhi and, in addition to a complex maze of neighbourhoods called polls, hosts some of the country&#39;s finest medieval Islamic architecture.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There is no problem of accommodations in Ahmedabad, India. In fact, there are numerous places to stay in Ahmedabad. Well equipped with all the modern facilities, the hotels over here provide you with great options to choose from. Depending on your budget and requirement, you can opt for luxury, deluxe or budget hotel. The hotels provide you with a world class ambience that conforms to international standards. The rooms are spacious and airy and also make adequate provision for ventilation. Fabulous service of the hotel is surely going to please you. The best thing is that, most of the hotels in Ahmedabad are located at a convenient point, which is few kilometres away from the airport and railway station.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong>: - Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel airport at Ahmedabad provides adequate air facilities. There are numerous domestic and international airlines that operate flights on a regular basis. Air India operates direct flights to USA and UK from Ahmedabad. Ahmedabad is connected to all the major cities like Mumbai, Delhi, Bangalore and Chennai via air.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail</strong>: - Ahmedabad is very well connected with rest parts of the country by train. There are regular trains to metropolitans like Delhi and Mumbai.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong>: - Ahmedabad has a wide network of roads. For travellers residing in other parts of Gujarat like Vadodra, Gandhinagar, Palitana, Rajkot, and Jamnagar, travelling to Ahmedabad is very convenient by road.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong>: - When it comes to public transportation in Ahmedabad, buses run by the Ahmedabad Municipal Transport Services (AMTS) are the most common means of transport used by people. Buses charge a very nominal price for their service. They don&#39;t have a fixed time schedule but operate on a regular basis. Another popular local transport consists of the shared rickshaws, which move from one point to another for getting more and more passengers. One can hire the private taxis, which are more often called the luxury taxis. The taxis can be hired for the full day for sightseeing purpose.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - RIDHI SIDHI - (FAMOUS FOR MISSAL PAV)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">2 - AMDO&#39;S &nbsp;KITCHEN - (FAMOUS FOR MOMOS, THUPKA &amp; THANTUK)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">3 - RASRANJAN - (FAMOUS FOR VARIETY OF DISHES)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">4 - BOMBAY STREET JOINT - (FAMOUS FOR STUFED ROLLS)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">5 - OM SAI - (FAMOUS FOR PARATHA)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">6 - AMBIKA DAALWADA - (FAMOUS FOR DAALWADA)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">7 - KAUSHAL&#39;S FOOD COURT - (FAMOUS FOR VARIET OF DISHES)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">8 - MEHTA&#39;S, NEAR VADILAL HOSPITAL, RAIPUR BHAJIA HOUSE&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;- [FAMOUS FOR KHAMAM (FLUFFY, SWEET &amp; SOUR DISH MADE OF BESAN)]</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">9 - KHAO GALI, NEXT TO LAW GARDEN - (FAMOUS FOR VARIETY OF STALS AND DISHES)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">10 - KHADAWALA&#39;S DALWADA CENTRE, NEAR GANDHIGRAM RAILWAY STATION - (FAMOUS FOR DALWADA)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">11 - MUNICIPAL MARKET (MM) - (FAMOUS FOR VARIETY OF DISHES)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">12 - CHOICE RESTAURANT,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;NEAR MM - (FAMOUS FOR PAV BHAJI, PIZZA, &amp; DOSA)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">13 - THORAN - (FAMOUS FOR GUJRATI THALI)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">14 - INDORE CHAT HOUSE,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;IN PALDI - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(147, 14, 31, 732, 'Andhra Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'HYDERABAD', 'charminar-896162_1920.jpg', 'charminar-896162_19201.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Hyderabad is the capital of southern India&#39;s Telangana state and from &lsquo;state of law&rsquo; Andra Pradesh. A major centre for the technology industry, it&rsquo;s a home of too many upscale restaurants and shops. The Charminar, a 16th century mosque whose 4 arches support towering minarets, is an old city landmark near the long-standing Laad Bazaar. The city of smiles, of lights, of a thousand faces, endearingly called the Pearl City, Hyderabad offers a variety of tourist attractions ranging from Heritage monuments, Lakes and Parks, Gardens and Resorts, Museums to delectable cuisine and a delightful shopping experience. To the traveller, Hyderabad offers a fascinating panorama of the past, with a richly mixed cultural and historical tradition spanning 400 colourful years. The Old City of Hyderabad is everything you might dream an Indian old city to be-narrow lanes thronged with markets, chai shops, wandering animals, auto rickshaws, a whirl of noise, colour, languages and religions dotted with stately old architecture in varying states of repair. Two unbelievably wealthy Muslim royal houses came and went from this city of pearls and diamonds, leaving a legacy of magnificent palaces, mosques and tombs. Other pole is far younger-its Hi-Tech City, or &#39;Cyberabad&#39;, out west, which since the 1990s has propelled the city into the modern world with its accoutrements of glittery malls, multiplexes, clubs, pubs and sleek restaurants to sit alongside the traditional biryani joints and teahouses. Also addressed as the Pearl City or the Biryani city, Hyderabad has plenty to offer you apart from just monuments.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">There is a range of places to stay in Hyderabad. The various types of accommodations available in Hyderabad for tourists range from high-end 5-star luxury/deluxe hotels to really low budget accommodation and the superior hotels for those who don&rsquo;t want to shell out that much money on their stay yet don&rsquo;t want to compromise on good services and facilities; and the third category is mid-ranged and budget hotels that are not tough on pocket and are affordable.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air</strong> - The Rajiv Gandhi International terminal, Hyderabad&rsquo;s international airport is well-connected with major cities across the globe. The airport also has a domestic terminal called NT Rama Rao which is connected to most of the Indian cities. Approximately 20 kilometres away from the city, the airport is situated in the Begumpet area. Almost all airlines fly daily from and to Hyderabad.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Boasting of a huge bus terminal, the city is well-connected to its neighbouring towns like Aurangabad, Bangalore, Mumbai, Kolkata, Chennai, Tirupati and Panaji. The bus terminal is managed and well-organised by Andhra Pradesh State Road Transport Corporation (APSRTC). One can choose from sleeper, deluxe, super deluxe, air-conditioned and Volvo buses that are operated by both state and private companies. The fare depends upon the type of the bus and the destination.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Train</strong> - There are three major railheads in the city, namely, Hyderabad Railway Station, Secunderabad Railway Station and Kachiguda Railway Station. These railheads connect major Indian cities like Bangalore, Chennai, New Delhi, Mumbai and Pune. Some of the popular trains that run daily from Hyderabad rail junctions are Kacheguda Express, Hyderabad Express, Charminar Express, Konark Express, Andhra Pradesh Express and Shatabdi Express.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Managed by the APSRTC body, Hyderabad city is well-connected by buses that take you to different parts of the city. Bus-stops are present in different areas of Hyderabad. The city&rsquo;s local train system also known as Multi-Modal Transport System (MMTS) is quite popular mode of transport. Apart from being the fastest medium to reach a place, it is also cheapest to travel via trains. While metered autos are available across the city. In case one wants a private vehicle can hire a prepaid taxi or a private cab to reach the destination. These are the most comfortable mode of transport in the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - HYDERABAD - [FAMOUS FOR PAYA; MAGHEZ MASALA (LAMB DISH); KHATTI DAL; QABOOLI BIRYANI; BURANI RAITA; LUKHMI (SQUARES OF MAIDA); HYDERABADI KHICHDI; KACHE GOSHT KI BIRYANI]&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">2 - PARADISE RESTAURANT, AT MAHTMA GANDHI ROAD, SAPPU BAGH APPARTMENT, JOGANI, KALASGUDA, SECUNDERABAD - (FAMOUS FOR HYDERABADI BIRYANI &amp; HYDERABADI HALEEM)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - PISTA HOUSE - [FAMOUS FOR HYDERABADI HALEEM (MADE FORM WHEAT &amp; MEAT, TOPPED WITH DRY FRUITS AND COOKED FOR SEVRAL HOURS]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - SARVI CAFE 555 - [FAMOUS FOR HYDERABADI HALEEM (MADE FORM WHEAT &amp; MEAT, TOPPED WITH DRY FRUITS AND COOKED FOR SEVRAL HOURS]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n5 - HOTEL SHABAD, IN CHAKHANDI AREA NEAR CHARMINAR - [FAMOUS FOR CHANA (MADE OF GOAT&#39;S TRIPE WITH LIVER AND KIDNEY&#39;S]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n6 - JEWEL OF NIZAM - [FAMOUS FOR HYDERABADI SALAN (POPULAR CURRY WITH HYDERABADI BIRYANI]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n7 - BIDRI, AT KASHMIR HEIGHTS, SHANBAGH&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;- [FAMOUS FOR HYDERABADI KORMA (MUTTON &amp; CHICKEN)]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n8 - BAWARCHI RESTAURANT, AT PLOT NO 66, RTE CROSS ROAD, OPPOSITE SANDHYA THEATRE, CHIKKADAPALLY - (FAMOUS FOR HYDERABAD CHICKEN 65)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n9 - HOTEL MADIN, NEAR CHARMINAR - (FAMOUS FOR SHEER KORMA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n10 - CHUTNEY&#39;S,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;IN BANJARA HILLS ROAD NO.3 - (FAMOUS FOR VARIETY OF DISHES)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n11 - HYDERABADI MIRAG - (FAMOUS FOR SPICY MEAT SOUP)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(148, 14, 31, 741, 'Jharkhand', 'INDIA', 'RANCHI', 'california-1597695_1280.jpg', 'california-1597695_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Set on a plateau at 700m and marginally cooler than the plains, Jharkhand&rsquo;s capital, Ranchi, was the summer capital of Bihar under the British. The city acts as a gateway to Betla National Park, and there are numerous waterfalls you can visit in the surrounding countryside. This state was formed on the 15th of November 2000, by carving out the districts form the Chhotanagpur and Santhal Parganas divisions of Bihar. Chhotanagpur plateau consists of the three smaller plateaus of Ranchi, Hazaribag, and Koderma.&nbsp;The city of Ranchi is located at an altitude of 654 meter above sea level on the plateau of Ranchi. Earlier the name of Ranchi District was Lohardaga. Ranchi, Capital of Jharkhand is also called as city of Waterfalls and lakes.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">For those searching for hotels in Ranchi can simply stay relaxed as the city has no dearth of accommodation options. Ranchi hotels offer one to experience a perfect amalgam of comfort and hospitality. There are luxury hotels, 3 star hotels, 2 star hotels and even cheap accommodation available in the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Air</strong>: - There is a landing airstrip popularly known as Birsa Munda Airport. Ranchi is connected with almost all the major cities of the country through air. Ranchi has frequent flight for Delhi, Mumbai, Kolkata, Bangalore, Patna &amp; Raipur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Railway</strong>: - Main station is Ranchi Junction. Ranchi railhead is well-connected to all important cities in India via regular trains.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Bus Service</strong>: - One can easily get regular buses to Ranchi from other major cities of the country. Ranchi is well connected to several cities in Jharkhand and Bihar by state road transport corporation buses.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SEVENTH HEAVEN, LOCATED AT SHRILOK, 4, HAZARIBAGH ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR SOUTH INDIAN FOOD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - ANGITHI RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT PEARL APARTMENT, CLUB ROAD, SIROM TOLY, NEW GARDEN, KANKA - (FAMOUS FOR ICE CREAM)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - BAWARCHI, LOCATED AT ASHOK NAGAR ROAD, NEAR MAPLE PLAZA - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN MOMOS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - AROMA FAMILY RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT OLD LOWADIH, PURULIA RD, SAMLONG - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN MANCHURIAN AND BUTTER PANEER MASALA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - JALAJOGA RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT ALBERT EKKA CHOWK, LINE TANK ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN CHILIAND CHICKEN KADHAI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - LAZEEZ RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT CENTRE POINT MARKET, BESIDE DAILY MARKET THANA - (FAMOUS FOR KABABS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - ADDICTION, LOCATED AT AC MARKET, GEL CHURCH COMPLEX, MAIN ROAD, KANKA - (FAMOUS FOR MOMOS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n8 - NEW RAJASTHAN KALEWALAYA, LOCATED AT LALPUR CHOWK - (FAMOUS FOR KESARIYA JALEBI, PYAZ KI KACHORI AND MISTI DAHI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>9 - MINT LEAF CAFE, LOCATED AT HINOO MAIN RD, SHIVPURI COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN BIRYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>10- PUNJAB SWEET HOUSE, LOCATED AT KADRU MAIN RD, HINDPIRI - (FAMOUS FOR KALAKAND AND RASOGULLA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>11 - BHAI BANDHU SWEETS, LOCATED AT BIRSA CHOWK, KATHALKOCHA - (FAMOUS FOR KALAKAND)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>12 - ANMOL SWEETS, LOCATED AT KATHOL MORE ROAD, PIPARTOLI, CHAPOTOLI - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>13 - SAPNA SWEETS, LOCATED AT ITKI, RANCHI - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA CHAT)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>14 - SWEET KESAR LADDU WALA, LOCATED AT BAHU BAZAR CHOWK, BAHU BAZAR, GUNGUTOLI, KANKA - (FAMOUS FOR PANEER PATTIES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(149, 14, 31, 1657, 'Chhattisgarh', 'INDIA', 'RAIPUR', 'bloom-1578783_1920.jpg', 'nut-165083.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Raipur, the capital of Chhattisgarh in central India, is a prominent industrial centre and one of the largest steel markets in the country. The city boasts of more than 200 steel rolling mills and six steel plants. Apart from steel, several other industries like coal, power, aluminium are also based Raipur. Aside from steel production Raipur is also known for producing rice and is known as the Rice Bowl of Chhattisgarh. Now developed as a major tourist destination, Raipur offers several sightseeing options. Raipur is India&rsquo;s fourth planned city after Chandigarh, Gandhinagar and Bhubaneshwar. Known for its modern infrastructure facilities, Raipur is turning out to be a major centre for the manufacturing, IT and bio-technology sectors. Raipur hosts several festivals and events and one of the prominent festivals is the festival of Pola which is dedicated to bulls. Raipur was founded by the Kalchuri King Ram Chandra of Raipur last quarter of the 14th century AD. Now, Raipur is the Headquarters of the District and Division of the same name centrally located in the newly formed State Chhattisgarh. &nbsp;Raipur is the biggest city of the Region and a fast developing important industrial centre.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are ample accommodation options in Raipur. And while there are several budget and mid-range hotels in the city, it is advisable to book your room in advance during the winter season because it is the peak season. Over the years, Raipur&rsquo;s palette has steadily expanded and restaurants here serve Indian versions of Chinese, American and Italian food.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Airways</strong>: - Raipur airport is well connected by regular flights to cities like Mumbai, Kolkata, Delhi, Pune, Hyderabad, Bhopal, Bhubaneshwar and many more. From the airport, taxi services are available.<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Railways</strong>: - The Raipur junction railway station is an important railhead. Trains from Chennai, Delhi, Mumbai, Nagpur, Bhubaneshwar, Bengaluru and Kolkata do halt at the station.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Roadways</strong>: - Raipur is well connected by road. One can take state run buses, which ply regularly from several cities of Chhattisgarh and neighbouring states.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong>: - A city bus service is provided by Raipur City Bus Limited (RCBL) for the intra-city travel. The company runs 40 buses out of which 32 are low floor Tata Starbus. Para transit in the form of auto-rickshaws and tuk-tuk are available all over the city. 100 new city buses under JNNURM have been inducted by Raipur Nagar Nigam Transport Limited (RNNTL), which serve the Raipur and connect Naya Raipur also.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - RAIPUR - (FAMOUS FOR DAL PITHI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - RAIPUR - (FAMOUS FOR KHEKSI CHANA DAL)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - RAIPUR - (FAMOUS FOR MOONG DAL HALWA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - RAIPUR - (FAMOUS FOR CHATTISGARHI KADAHI PAKODA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n5 - RAIPUR - [FAMOUS FOR CHAPRA (CUSTOMISED CHUTNEY)]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n6 - RAIPUR - (FAMOUS FOR RICE CHIILA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n7 - RAIPUR - [FAMOUS FOR MUTHIYA (MADE BY RICE, FLOUR, SEASOME SEEDS, MUSTARD SEEDS, RED BEAN STEW)]&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(150, 14, 31, 751, 'Punjab', 'INDIA', 'AMRITSAR', 'travel-973301_1920.jpg', 'travel-973301_19201.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Amritsar city situated in northern Punjab state of north-western India lies about 25 kms east of the border with Pakistan. Amritsar is an important city in Punjab and is a major commercial, cultural, and transportation centre. It is also the centre of Sikhism and the site of the Sikh&rsquo;s principal place of worship. Founded in 1577 by the fourth Sikh guru, Ram Das, Amritsar is home to Sikhism&rsquo;s holiest shrine, the spectacular Golden Temple, one of India&rsquo;s most serene and humbling sights. The same cannot be said for the hyperactive streets surrounding the temple. Amritsar is divided in two by a tangle of railway lines. The old city, containing the Golden Temple and other historic sites and bound by 12 medieval gates, is southeast of the railway lines. This is a fascinating area to explore, with a capillary network of narrow bazaars that seems to float between the centuries. To the north of the railway lines, modern Amritsar has grown up in haphazard fashion around a scattering of colonial-era boulevards. Gleaming malls and upmarket hotels stand testament to the prosperity of the city, but the hectic traffic makes this area hard to love at street level. Crossing between the old and new cities is best done by cycle-rickshaw, but once in the old city, walking is often the quickest way to get around.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">It is a popular tourist destination and has over 120 hotels with accommodation ranging from luxurious resorts to budget stay options in Amritsar. There are several five star luxury hotels. Four and three star hotels are available in plenty. If you are on the lookout for more budget options then Amritsar has several hotels that will fit your needs and budget. Cheaper accommodation is available around the temple area and Tourist Guest House is an ideal location if all that you need is a clean bed and a shower.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Air</strong> - Amritsar&#39;s international airport, Sri Guru Ram Dass Jee International Airport, has more than 250 domestic and international flights during the week with daily connections to Delhi, Mumbai, Kolkata, Chennai, Bangalore, and Srinagar etc. in India and international flights to London, Birmingham, Melbourne and Sydney via Delhi.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Train </strong>- Amritsar is well connected by rail to almost all major cities in India. Amritsar railway station is the main terminal station. There is a special train that runs west to Wagah, which is the last station on the border in India before continuing on to Pakistan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Road</strong> - Amritsar is located on the historic Grand Trunk Road, also known as National Highway 1, and therefore very well connected to the road network. Daily bus services run to and from Ambala, Patiala, Delhi, Chandigarh and Jammu. There is also a bus service to Lahore, 35 kms away, which is the only overland connection between India and Pakistan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Amritsar is a small city and as such auto-rickshaws and cycle-rickshaws are common and cheap modes of transport in the city. There is a free bus service running between the train station and the Golden Temple, which is operated by the Golden Temple Trust. One can hire a car in Amritsar to travel within and around the city. There are several car rental companies in the city that rent chauffeur driven cars as well as cars for self-drive.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - WITHIN GOLDEN TEMPLE PREMISE, GOlDEN TEMPLE ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR GURU KA LANGAR)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - BHARWAN DA DHABA, CLOSE TO GOLDEN TEMPLE - [(FAMOUS &nbsp;FOR MAKKE DI ROTI &amp; SARSO DA SAAG. STUUFED KULCHAS &amp; CHOLE)]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - PAL DHABA, NEAR HATHI GATE - (FAMOUS FOR PAYA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - BEERA CHICKEN CORNER - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN TIKKA TANDOORI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n5 - ADARSH MEAT SHOP, CLOSE TO C- BLOCK MARKET COMPLEX NEAR ROSE GARDEN - [FAMOUS FOR CHAPAT MUTTON]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n6 - AHUJA, NEAR HINDU COLLEGE, DURGIAN TEMPLE - (FAMOUS FOR LASSI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n7 - MAMME DA DHABA - [FAMOUS FOR BHEJA FRY]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n8 - SHARMA SWEET SHOP - [FAMOUS FOR JALEBI]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n9 - HALL BAZAR - [FAMOUS FOR FRUIT CREAM AND KULFI]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n10 - KANHA SWEETS - [FAMOUS FOR PINNI (DESERT MADE FROM LENTIL AND JAGGERY]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n11 - NOVELTY SWEETS - (FAMOUS FOR GAJAR KA HALWA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n12 - GIANI TEA STALL - (FAMOUS FOR TEA)</p>\r\n', ''),
(151, 14, 31, 739, 'Haryana', 'INDIA', 'GURGAON', 'transportation-1572349_1920.jpg', 'transportation-1572349_19201.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Gurgaon, the second largest city in Haryana, is one of the most important industrial and financial hubs of the nation. Gurgaon is also known as Guru Gram or Guru Gaon, which was named after revered teacher Dronacharya of epic Mahabharata. It is believed that Dronacharya was gifted this ancestral village by his disciples, the Pandavas and Kauravas. He gave spiritual instructions to them at this place. It has modern facilities and a planned infrastructure. The public-private sector partnership model in real estate development has been the major force behind Gurgaon&#39;s emergence as the corporate capital. It has developed more because of availability of ample connectivity options to the Capital. From a dusty, little-visited suburb of Delhi, Gurgaon is today the National Capital Region&#39;s glitziest outpost. With a skyline that evokes comparisons with Hong Kong and Singapore, Gurgaon&#39;s funky high-rises, malls and entertainment complexes have become the preferred hubs for technology companies and young professionals. Not surprisingly the city has a thriving clubbing and party scene. Apart from being a city with throbbing commercial activities, Gurgaon is also blessed with quite a few fascinating tourist attractions. The city is located on the border with New Delhi to its north east.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">In the past few years, the number of hotels in Gurgaon has gone up rapidly. Having come a long way from being just another commercial hub, Gurgaon often termed as a quick escape from the bustling capital Delhi, is now dotted with numerous entertainment hubs, cultural venues, shopping malls, and hotels. Whether you&rsquo;re on a business trip or on a laidback vacation, Gurgaon has accommodation for all kinds of travellers.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Roadways</strong>: - The major highway that links Gurgaon is National Highway 8, the road that runs from Delhi to Mumbai. Gurgaon bus terminal, managed by Haryana Roadways, is a busy bus station in the city that provides bus connectivity, both private and government, to other cities in Haryana and neighbouring states like Delhi, Uttar Pradesh and other cities like Chandigarh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Railways</strong>: - Gurgaon railway station operated by Northern Railway of Indian Railways. The rail station that forms a part of the larger Indian railways network, where trains connect Gurgaon to Delhi and other important cities in India like Mumbai, Kolkata, Ahmadabad and Jaipur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Airways</strong>: - Gurgaon is served by Indira Gandhi International Airport, though the airport is just outside the city limits and located within the jurisdiction of Delhi near National Highway No. 8.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Getting Around</strong>: - Public transit in Gurgaon is mostly provided by government buses, Rapid Metro and Delhi Metro. There are ten metro stations in Gurgaon. Private buses &amp; vans, reserved and shared auto rickshaws also ply in the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - PAPPU, LOCATED ON 16-F MADANPURI ROAD, NEW COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR FISH FRY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - SARDAR JALEBI WALE, LOCATED AT ROSHAN PURA - (FAMOUS FOR JALEBI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - GANDHI JI PAKODE WALE, LOCATED AT SADAR BAZAR - (FAMOUS FOR PAKODAS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - 21 GUNS SALUTE, LOCATED AT SECTOR-29 - (FAMOUS FOR MURG SHAIKAWATI KEBAB, MALAI KOFTA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - BOMBAY BEST PAO BHAJI, LOCATED AT SECTOR-4 - (FAMOUS FOR PAO BHAJI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - OM SWEETS, LOCATED AT ARJUN NAGAR&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;- (FAMOUS FOR GOLGAPPAS, STRAWBERRY MILKSHAKE, CHOCOLATE PASTRY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - SINGH CHICKEN CORNER, LOCATED AT OLD DELHI ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN, BUTTER ROTI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>8 - THE MONK, LOCATED AT GALAXY MALL, SECTOR-15 - (FAMOUS FOR FRIED FLAT RICE NOODLE WITH FISH IN OYSTER GARLIC SAUCE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>9 - AGGARWAL SWEET &amp; SNACKS, LOCATED AT OPP HANUMAN MANDIR, OLD DELHI GURGAON ROAD, DUNDAHERA, GURUGRAM - (FAMOUS FOR CHOWMIEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>10 - KISHU DI HATTI, LOCATED AT NEW COLONY, SECTOR 7, GURUGRAM - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSAS WITH CHOLEY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>11 - REWARI SWEETS, LOCATED AT NEAR HEAD POST OFFICE, SADAR BAZAR RD, JACOBPURA, SECTOR 12, GURUGRAM - (FAMOUS FOR KHOYA BURFI AND GAJAR KA HALUWA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n12 - SANTOSH SWEETS, LOCATED AT PATAUDI CHOWK, BASAI ROAD, VIR NAGAR, GURUGRAM - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>13 - SANGAM SWEETS &amp; SNACKS, LOCATED AT NEAR OBC BANK, OPP. H-BLOCK, PALAM VIHAR, CHOMA, GURUGRAM - (FAMOUS FOR CHOLE BHATURE)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n14 - LAL JI SWEETS, LOCATED AT KHANDSA ROAD, SHIVJI PARK COLONY, SECTOR 10A, GURUGRAM - (FAMOUS FOR PASTRIES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>15 - DANA CHOGA, LOCATED AT NO.F-6, QUTUB PLAZA, DLF CITY PHASE-1, BLOCK A, SECTOR 26A, GURUGRAM - (FAMOUS FOR NORTH INDIAN FOOD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>14 - KITCHEN OF AWADH, LOCATED AT A-208, SUPERMART-1 DLF PHASE-4, GURUGRAM - (FAMOUS FOR KEBAB WITH PARANTHA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n15 - GREENS SWEETS &amp; RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT SCF 23, SARASWATI VIHAR SHOPPING, MEHRAULI GURGAON ROAD, DLF CHAKKARPUR, SECTOR 28, GURUGRAM - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>16 - RASOI THE FOOD EXPRESS, LOCATED AT