(152, 14, 31, 1653, 'Uttarakhand', 'INDIA', 'DEHRADUN', 'dehra.jpg', 'dehra1.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Nestled in the mountain ranges of the Himalayas, Dehradun is the capital of Uttarakhand. It is one of the most beautiful resorts in the sub mountain tracks of India, known for its scenic surroundings. The name Dehradun is a collection of two words &quot;dera&quot; meaning camp and &quot;dun&quot; meaning valley. Said to be one of the oldest cities in India, it is believed that Lord Rama and his brother did penance here for killing Ravana, the demon king. During the 17th and 18th centuries Dehradun changed hands several times: Guru Ram Rai retreated here from Punjab, the Mughal Governor Najib-ud-Daula occupied it from 1757-1770 and the Gorkhas overran it on their westward expansion before ceding it to the British in 1815. Under the British, Dehradun became an elite town with many a fine institutions like Forest Research Institute, Doon School and Welham Schools for girls and boys, many more, like the ONGC and Wadia Institute of Himalayan Studies, were added in time. Dehradun has now become an important tourist destination. The district is situated in the north-west corner of the state. It is bounded on the north and to some distance in the north-west by the district of Uttarkashi, in the east by the district Tehri Garhwal and Pauri-Garhwal. In the south it is bounded by the district of Saharanpur (Uttar Pradesh). At its southern tip is touching the boundary of district Haridwar. Its western boundary adjoins the Sirmur district of Himachal Pradesh with the rivers Tons and Yamuna separating the two.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Dehradun offers a wide choice in places to stay and the accommodation hare ranges from luxury to budget hotels. The deluxe hotels will provide well-equipped rooms and modern facilities with upgrade service. Most of the inexpensive hotels are located around the railway station and in the Clock Tower area near the centre of town. If you have budget constraints then check out budget with basic facilities like. Some good budget hotels in Dehradun are Doon Regency Hotel, Relax Hotel, Grand Hotel and Siddarth Residency.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong>: - Jolly Grant Airport is the nearest Airport to Dehradun city of Uttarakhand state. It is situated 25 kms from Dehradun city with motor able roads. Taxis are easily available from Jolly Grant Airport to Dehradun. Jolly Grant Airport is well connected to Delhi with daily flights.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Railway</strong>: - Dehradun is well connected with railways and you can reach up to Dehradun by train from major cities of India. There are two trains that run daily between Delhi to Dehradun and vice-versa. Shatabdi Express and Mussoorie Express are the two major trains connecting Dehradun with major cities of India like Amritsar, Howrah, Bombay, Delhi, Lucknow, Varanasi etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong>: - Dehradun is well connected with all major road transportation facilities. Luxury and normal Buses to Dehradun are easily available from ISBT Kashmiri Gate, Delhi. Buses and Taxis to Dehradun are also available from major destinations of Uttarakhand state. Dehradun is connected with National Highway 72 making it easier to access.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transportation</strong>: - The local modes of transport are local buses, auto rickshaws, shared mini-cabs, hired private cabs.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - THE BUFFET SNACKS SHOPS, AT RAJPUR ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR FAST FOOD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - KC MOMOS AND SOUP BAR, AT JARKHANA RAJPUR ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR MOMOS AND SOUPS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - BUN TIKI WALA, AT DWARKA CHOWK STORE - (FAMOUS FOR BUN TIKKIS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - CHETAN POORI WALA, AT HANUMAN CHOWK - (FAMOUS FOR POORI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - MADRAS DOSA HUT, AT PARADE GROUND - (FAMOUS FOR DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - GAYLORD ICE CREAM PARLOUR, AT PALTAN BAZAR - (FAMOUS FOR ICE CREAMS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - CHAAT WALI GALI, AT CLOCK TOWER - (FAMOUS FOR CHAAT AND GOLGAPPA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - BOBBY FAST FOOD CORNER, AT GANDHI CHOWK - (FAMOUS FOR NON VEG MOMO AND CHOWMIEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>9 - GARHI CANTT - (FAMOUS FOR MOMOS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>10 - BUS STAND - (FAMOUS FOR SYRUPY THUPKA FOOD AND MOMOS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>11 - ELLORA - (FAMOUS FOR CAKES AND PASTRIES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>12 - YETI RESTAURANT - (FAMOUS FOR CHINESE CUSINE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>13 - CHICKEN CORNER - (FAMOUS FOR BIRYANI AND KEBABS)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '');
