(197, 14, 31, 1655, 'Jammu & Kashmir', 'INDIA', 'ANANTNAG', 'mountains-1622731_640.jpg', 'mountains-1622731_12802.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Anantnag District, known as the commercial capital of Jammu &amp; Kashmir, is located in the south-western part of the Kashmir valley. The destination is considered to be one of the most developed regions in the valley of Kashmir. In 5000 B.C, this region became a market town and gained title of being the earliest site of urban development and one of the oldest towns of the world. Anantnag is surrounded by various cities like Srinagar, Kargil, Pulwama, Doda and Kishtawar. The district has derived its name from the popular folklore according to which Lord Shiva discarded all the valuables while on his way to the Amarnath Cave. The place where he dropped numerous snakes has been named as Anantnag. Presently Anantnag is connected to three tehsil, namely Gool Gulab Garh, Doda and Budhal. Anantnag is popular among tourists for its numerous shrines, which are of religious importance to both Hindus and Muslims. Anantnag features a number of sites of tourist interest like lakes, hot springs, shrines and temples. There are innumerable natural springs and two sulphur springs in Anantnag. Tourists mainly visit the springs of Nag Bal, Malik Nag and Salag Nag. Anantnag does not have any ancient building or archaeological site at present because most of their architectural monuments witnessed destruction during the era of Sultan Sikander.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Anantnag is a major tourist spot in India and rental accommodation is also easily available. One can easily find a range of luxury and budget hotels as well as private accommodation and guest house at affordable prices. These accommodations are equipped with a lot of features and amenities including spacious rooms, beautiful interiors, modern appliances, wide TV screens, phones, attractive furniture and much more. However, it is advisable to make bookings in advance in order to avoid last minute hassle and inconvenience.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Srinagar Airport, also known as Sheikh ul Alam Airport, is the closest air base from Anantnag. The airport is located at a distance of 62 kms from the destination.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail </strong>- The district of Anantnag has got a railway station, which is connected to few important cities of the state. However, Jammu Tawi railway station is a major railhead of the state, which is well connected to major Indian cities such as New Delhi, Mumbai, Chennai, Chandigarh and Trivandrum, to mention a few.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Anantnag is directly connected to cities like Jammu and Srinagar via roadways. Jammu is located at a distance of 237 kms from Anantnag and takes around 4 hours to cover the distance. Buses and taxis are easily available for Anantnag from above mentioned cities. Tourists can also avail luxury private buses for Anantnag at a reasonable cost.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - AMIGOS, LOCATED AT KP RD, QAZI BAGH - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - HAT TRICK, LOCATED AT KP RD, NAI BASTI - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN BIRYANI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - CREAM BELL, LOCATED AT KP RD, NAI BASTI - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;ICE CREAMS)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(198, 14, 31, 1655, 'Jammu & Kashmir', 'INDIA', 'BARAMULLA', 'ice-curtain-16558_640.jpg', 'ice-curtain-16558_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Baramulla District, one of the 22 districts of the state of Jammu &amp; Kashmir, is further divided into 8 tehsils and 16 blocks and covers a total area of more than 4190 sq kms. This district shares its borders with Pakistan occupied Kashmir on its western side. Baramulla is situated to the south of the town of Kupwara and north of Pooch and Budgam with Srinagar and Ladakh bordering its eastern side. This ancient city was founded by Raja Bhimsina in 2306 BC. The region was visited by the great Mughal emperor Akbar in 1508. Jahangir, in appreciation of the beauty of the place, decided to stay here while on his journey to the Kashmir Valley. Hieun T&rsquo;Sang, the well known Chinese traveller, had also once visited the district of Baramulla. This district has derived its name from two Sanskrit words, namely &lsquo;Varrah&rsquo;, meaning Boar, and &lsquo;Mul&rsquo;, meaning Molar, which together mean &lsquo;boar molar&rsquo;. The legend behind the name of the place has been written in the Nilmathpurna, the ancient epic of Kashmir. Baramulla is popular among tourists for its gurudwaras, temples, monasteries, and shrines. The third largest city of Jammu &amp; Kashmir, Baramullah has incredibly magnificent views of open valleys in the east and an enormous chain of mountains on the west. This city is one of the most popular destinations for adventurous as well as religious tourists. Remaining snow clad and facing extremely chilling below freezing temperatures, Baramulla has spectacular views and out-of-the-world picturesque beauty during winters as well.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">There are several hotels and huts that cater to the needs of the tourists. There are hotels that suit the varying budgets of the tourists to Baramulla. All the basic facilities are available to make the stay in Baramulla comfortable. Tourists may check out for accommodation options run by the Jammu and Kashmir Tourist Development Corporation or the private parties. It is advisable to go in advance reservations in the peak seasons. Delicious and hygienic food is easily available in the restaurants and the eateries of Baramulla. In the non vegetarian food there is the traditional dish of Rogan Josh that must taste.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air </strong>- The Srinagar Airport is the nearest air base as it is located at a distance of 66 kms from Baramulla. This airport, otherwise known as the Sheikh ul Alam Airport, is well connected to major cities in India, including New Delhi, Chandigarh, Mumbai, and Shimla, to name a few.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Rail </strong>- The Jammu Tawi railway station is the nearest railhead to Baramulla, situated at a distance of 360 kms. This railway junction is well connected to major towns and cities in India such as New Delhi, Goa, Chennai, Mumbai, Ludhiana, Kolkata, Jalandhar, Agra to name a few.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Road </strong>- Travellers planning a trip to Baramulla can reach the destination via road. Buses for Baramulla are easily available from neighbouring areas, namely Kargil, Jammu and Srinagar. Travellers can first take direct buses to the above mentioned regions from New Delhi, Chandigarh, Ambala, Ludhiana, Shimla and Manali.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(199, 14, 31, 751, 'Punjab', 'INDIA', 'BHATINDA', 'sikh-658513_640.jpg', 'sikh-658513_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Bathinda District is situated in the Southern part of Punjab State in the heart of Malwa region. The district is surrounded with Sirsa and Fatehabad of Haryana State in the South, Sangrur and Mansa district in the East, Moga in the Northeast and Faridkot &amp; Muktsar in the Northwest. Bathinda, named after the Bhati Rajput kings, is one of the oldest cities in Punjab, India and the current administrative headquarters of Bathinda District. It is in northwestern India in the Malwa Region, 225 kms west of the capital city of Chandigarh. Bathinda is nicknamed the &#39;City of Lakes&#39; and was once known as Tabar-e-Hind, meaning the Gateway to India. The first empress of India, Razia Sultan was imprisoned in the Qila Mubarak fort in Bathinda. Bathinda is home to two modern thermal power plants, Guru Nanak Dev Thermal Plant and Guru Hargobind Thermal Plant at Lehra Mohabbat. The city has a fertilizer plant, a large oil refinery, a zoo, and a historic Qila Mubarak fort. Bathinda is one of the largest food grain and cotton markets in northern India; the area around Bathinda is a prolific grape growing area. It is one of the leading cities in education in Punjab. The etymology of &quot;Bathinda&quot; is uncertain. According to Khalifa Muhammad Hassan, author of History of Patiala, the ancient name of the city was Bikramgarh. According to Ibn Battuta it was known as Batrind. It is generally believed that Bathinda was built by Bhati Rajput kings, who were the rulers of Punjab in 6th century AD. They called the city Whatinda or Bitunda after their surnames which finally become known as Bhatinda.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">If budget allows, stay in the Bahia Fort Hotel which is now a four star hotel. Bahia fort was once Patiala State Maharaja Bhupinder Singh&#39;s official residence. One can also find budget and mid range hotels here.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest airport from Bhatinda is Amritsar airport, which is 182 kms from Bhatinda. From the airport one can take bus or taxi to Bhatinda. Amritsar airport has many flights to other cities.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Train </strong>- Bhatinda City is well connected with railways network and one can reach here by a variety of trains like Punjab Mail, FZR Janta Express, Udayan Abha Tufan Express, ADI, Jat Express, Okha ADI Pass etc. Almost all of these trains run daily from the city or pass through here.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Road </strong>- Bhatinda is well connected by roads with all neighbouring and major cities of India from where one can reach the city by taxies or buses. There are many travel agencies that operate daily bus and taxi service to the city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Buses and autos are easily available. Alternately, one can also book a taxi.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(200, 14, 31, 1653, 'Uttarakhand', 'INDIA', 'CHAMOLI', 'everest-1199431_640.jpg', 'everest-1199431_1280.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Chamoli District is the second largest district of Uttarakhand and is bounded by the Tibet region to the north and by the districts of Pithoragarh and Bageshwar to the east, Almora to the south, Garhwal to the southwest, Rudraprayag to the west and Uttarkashi to the northwest. The administrative headquarters of the district is Gopeshwar. Chamoli, the abode of Gods, reputed for its shrines and temples, birth place of &#39;Chipko Movement &#39; with its strategic significance is one of the hill district of Uttarakhand. Chamoli proved itself &quot; the most spectacular in its natural assets; be it maintain scenery, valley aspects, water-edges, floristic varieties, dramatic landform or the climatic cardinalities &quot;. Chamoli hosts a variety of destinations of pilgrim and tourists&#39; interest like Badrinath, Hemkund Sahib, Valley of Flowers and Auli. Chamoli proved itself &quot;the most spectacular in its natural assets; be it maintain scenery, valley aspects, water-edges, floristic varieties, dramatic landform or the climatic cardinalities&quot;. The district is also inhabited by Bhotiya ethnic group who adhere to Hinduism.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Chamoli, although a small place, offers various accommodation options to chose from. It houses budget hotels and guest houses to luxury and premium hotels. Nearby places like Auli, Gopeshwar and Badrinath also offers some fine accommodations. One can also opt for lodges or Dharamshala while staying in Chamoli.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air </strong>- The closest airport is located at Dehradun. The Jolly Grant Airport is situated around 227 kms from the place. The airport has frequent flight connectivity to Delhi and this is the most viable option for those who are arriving by air.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail </strong>- The closest major railhead is located at the town of Haridwar and this is the most suitable choice for those travellers who are planning to arrive by rail. Haridwar has rail services from many cities and one can reach the place from Delhi, Lucknow and Dehradun easily.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road </strong>- The town is connected by state run buses and these are affordable and frequent. Buses ply to Chamoli Gopeshwar from places such as Haridwar Dehradun, and Rishikesh regularly. Tickets from Dehradun cost around Rs. 150/- Buses are not comfortable and are often crowded as they are used by many tourists who travel through this route.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport</strong> - The place offers many ways to commute from one spot to another. Buses run regularly connecting many cities and are a cheap mode of transport. One can also take auto-rickshaws that are reliable and easy to find. However, the more sturdy form of transportation is either a taxi or hiring a private car which is expensive but very easy for commuting.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - Chamoli - (famous for Pinalu Gutuk is made of fried potato, Bal Mithai is sweet made of khoya and sugar)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(201, 14, 31, 1658, 'Odisha', 'INDIA', 'CUTTACK', 'jodhpur-1215239_6402.jpg', 'jodhpur-1215239_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Cuttack is one of Orissa&#39;s oldest cities Cuttack is a bustling commercial centre, situated on the delta formed by the Mahanadi and Kathjori rivers. The legendary engineering skills of the ancient Orissans are not only featured in their wonderful temples but also can be seen in the 11th century AD stone embankments on the Kathjori River. The ruins of the Barabati fort, on the bank of the Mahanadi, evoke memories of bygone days, while the fort&#39;s location is home to a modern stadium which rings with the sounds of sports events and cultural programmes today. Cuttack also offers excellent shopping facilities. Handicrafts and textiles, both in silk and cotton from the Cuttack region and elsewhere in Orissa are available in the state emporia. But Cuttack is best known for its excellent silver filigree work which is fashioned into exquisite jewellery, utensils and decorative items. Cuttack is 30 kms from Bhubaneswar. With a legacy that can be traced back over a 1000 years, it is the business capital of the state of Odisha. The craftsmanship of the people of this city in horn works, patta chitra, terracotta, wood carving and art leather, are much sought-after. The various monuments scattered across Cuttack are glowing testaments to these skills, which have been handed down through the centuries.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Take the pick from luxury to budget hotels that will offer comfortable stay. Conveniently located in the heart of the city, Hotel Ashoka is one of the best in budget hotels. Hotel Sagar Shree is a fine blend of traditional and contemporary sophistication. Located close to the commercial and shopping districts it is a good option for the busy traveller. Hotel Manorama Plaza is suitable for both business executives and tourists. The hotel is ideally located near various places of interest and shopping centres. Other hotels that offer a comfortable stay are Hotel Akbari Continental, Hotel Dwarika and Hotel Bombay Inn.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest airport to Cuttack is the Biju Patnaik Airport at Bhubaneswar. This prominent airport is connected by several flights to all major parts of the country. Several flights to the metros and many other cities including Kolkata, Delhi, Mumbai, Chennai, Hyderabad and Visakhapatnam ply on a regular basis to and from this airport.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail </strong>- Cuttack has a bustling railway station that connects it to some of the major towns and cities located in and outside of Odisha. There are several trains that connect Cuttack to different parts of the country and carry passengers in and out of the city every day.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>By Road</strong> - National Highway No. 5 passes through Cuttack and makes it the most accessible city of Orissa. The city is connected by road with Bhubaneswar, Puri, and other important cities of the state. Cuttack is connected through a smooth network of National Highways with the rest of the country. There are regular buses that ply between Cuttack and other cities in and around Odisha.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Hired cars, autos, and cycle rickshaws are common ways to travel in the town. There are town buses also which cover some parts of the city. Dream Team Sahara and OSRTC ply buses in the city, making the life of tourists and natives easier. Currently, Badambadi Bus Stand at Badambadi colony serves as one of the important bus stops of the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - CUTTACK - {FAMOUS FOR PRAWN MALAI CURRY IS A CURRY MADE FROM &nbsp;PRAWNS AND COCONUT MILK ; CHICKEN IN SILKY SPINACH CURRY IS A DISH MADE FROM &nbsp;(CHICKEN PIECES ARE COOKED IN MILDLY-SPICED SPINACH GRAVY, PEPPERCORNS, CLOVES, CARDAMOM, ONIONS, GARLIC, GINGER, CORIANDER POWDER, CUMIN POWDER, GARAM MASALA, &nbsp;TOMATOES, SALT AND BUTTER ; MACHER KALIA WITH ALOO IS A DISH MADE FROM MURREL FISH, RAW MANGO TURMERIC, RED CHILLIES, GREEN CHILLIES, OIL, GARLIC, GINGER, CUMIN SEEDS, CORIANDER SEEDS, ONION, CINNAMON, BAY LEAF, YOGURT, AND SALT, SERVED WITH RICE OR ROTI ; BHINDI BHAJA IS A DISH MADE FROM LADIES FINGER, TOMATO, ONION, CURRY LEAVES, GREEN CHILI, GARLIC, CLOVES, TURMERIC POWDER, MUSTARD SEEDS, ANISEED, URAD DAL, ASAFOETIDA AND SERVED WITH RICE OR ROTI ; DALMA IS A DISH MADE FROM VARIOUS DAALS( IS PIGEON PEA)AND VEGETABLES (PAPITA, POTATO, BRINJAL, DRUMSTICK, ARBI, BEANS, RAW BANANA, PUMPKIN AND TOMATO) ONION, MUSTARD SEED, CUMIN SEED, TURMERIC POWDER, BAY LEAF, CHILLI ; RASABALI IS A SWEET DISH MADE FROM PANEER ; BAKING SODA, SUJI, MAIDA, SUGAR, CHHENNA, MILK, SAFFRON, CARDAMOM, ALMONDS ; CHHENA JALEBI IS A SWEET DISH MADE FROM COTTAGE CHEESE AND SOAKED IN SUGAR SYRUP}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - BARABATI RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT MASIK PATNA COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN BUTTER MASALA WITH BUTTER NAAN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - CUTTACK,ORISSA, VYANJAN RESTAURANT&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT NAYA SADAK - (FAMOUS FOR SOUTH INDIAN FOOD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - NANKING, LOCATED AT BADAMBADI COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR CHILLY CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - DAMAS FOOD JUNCTION, LOCATED AT C-1112, SECTOR 6, C D A - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;MASALA DOSA AND SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - ROYALE, LOCATED AT BUXI BAZAAR - (FAMOUS FOR MUTTON BIRYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - DAMA MAHARAJ, LOCATED AT BUXI BAZAAR - (FAMOUS FOR PAPDI CHAT AND KACHORI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>8 - KICHEN, LOCATED AT BIJU PATNAIK COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR PANEER ROLL)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>9 - TAPAN FAST FOOD, LOCATED AT LIC COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR EGG AND CHICKEN ROLLS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>10 - NANDA GOPAL SWEETS, LOCATED AT NUAPATNA ROAD, NUAPATNA, MAACHHUA BAZA - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSAS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>11 - CUTTACK,ORISSA, CAFE CORNER, LOCATED AT STADIUM ROAD, BIJU PATNAIK COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN PATTIES, SHAKES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>12 - KABAB POINT, LOCATED AT ORIYA BAZAR - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN SPRING ROLLS)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(202, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'DEOGHAR', 'murti-1129933_640.jpg', 'murti-1129933_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Deoghar, a popular religious destination is blessed with one of the 12 Jyotirlinga temples known as temple Baidyanath. Deoghar is located on an undulated landscape and has small hillocks surrounded with jungles. An egg shaped River Island; Srirangapatna has immense historical as well as religious importance with its rather interesting mix of tourist attractions like temples, tombs, military warehouses and palaces. Once the capital of Hyder Ali and Tipu Sultan, this city is home to multiple sites and is of historical relevance. The multiple temples here are also major attractions. Yamunajor and Dharua are two rivers which flow near Deoghar. The scenic beauty of the place and good weather makes it a popular destination from the point of view of health tourism. Numerous Buddhist ruins are also located nearby.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Luxury hotels, 3 star hotels, 2 star hotels and even cheap accommodation are available in the city. Hotels here bring for its guests a perfectly comfy stay in the sacred city. The string of various amenities and delightful culinary facilities makes this place perfect for a restful stay for pilgrims.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest airport is Patna which is connected to other major cities of India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail</strong> - Baidyanath Dham is the nearest railway station and Jasidih is the main railway junction. It is on the Howrah Patna Delhi Line. Daily passenger trains also run from the cities nearby.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road </strong>- Buses are available on a regular basis from all surrounding cities as well as other major cities. It is well connected to Kolkata, Ranchi and Patna. It is easily accessible as it situated near GT Road. Regular buses are available from surrounding towns.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Getting around Deoghar </strong>- Unmetered Taxis, Scooters, Cycle Rickshaws are available. Travelling locally can also be facilitated by rickshaws, tonga-walas and taxis.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(204, 14, 31, 741, 'Jharkhand', 'INDIA', 'DHANBAD', 'coal-1626401_640.jpg', 'coal-1626401_1280.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Dhanbad is the Coal Capital of India and ranks 79th amongst the fastest growing cities in the world. While the city&rsquo;s earlier history remains a mystery, its present development is no secret to the world as it lies at the centre of the heart of the country&rsquo;s richest coal fields. Dhanbad is the renowned mining city of Jharkhand, Dhanbad, harbours richest coal fields of India. It is surrounded by Bokaro and Giridih districts in the West. Dumka and Giridih bound the city on the North while Purulia District is on the East and South. Damodar River plays a very important role throughout the coal field area. Barakar River also flows across the city. Some other small rivers include Gobai, the Irji, the Khudia and the Katri. Various socio cultural, industrial and educational institutes have made Dhanbad popular throughout India. 100850 acres of the district are covered with hillocks while 56454 acres are laid out with sprawling forests. Red soil found in this area is not much useful for agriculture. Pisciculture and sericulture are practices by many people of this region.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Accommodation is good in Dhanbad as this city is commercial hub and effect of that is visible on its all round development. Dhanbad has various budget and luxurious hotels where one can easily stay as per budget and aspirations.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Dhanbad lacks an airport of its own. An airstrip is planned near Barwadda. There are few airports close to the city. Dhanbad is 175 kms from Birsa Munda Airport Ranchi, 215 kms from Gaya Airport, 269 kms from Netaji Subhas Chandra Bose International Airport, Kolkata and 320 kms from Lok Nayak Jayaprakash Airport, Patna.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail </strong>- Dhanbad is well connected by railways to major cities of India like Delhi, Mumbai, Kolkata, Chennai, Ahmedabad, Hyderabad and many more. Almost all the states of India are connected through rail routes. AC double-decker train which is introduced for the first time in India connects Howrah and Dhanbad.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- National Highway 2 and National Highway 32 run across Dhanbad. These two major highways connect the mining capital with various places. NH 2 being a part of Golden Quadrilateral connects Dhanbad to Delhi. NH 32 connects to Bokaro and Jamshedpur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- One can travel around in auto-rickshaws, minibuses or hired cabs. Taking a minibus is the most economical option. State and private buses also help in intercity travelling.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SHAWARMA STREET, LOCATED AT &nbsp;IIT (ISM), MAIN ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR SHAWARMA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - SRIYAM, LOCATED AT MIDDLE SCHOOL ROAD, LAHABANI ROAD, DHAIYA - (FAMOUS FOR MASALA BHINDI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - WAIKIKI, LOCATED AT NH 32, BANK MORE - (FAMOUS FOR SOUTH INDIAN FOOD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - SHAHI DARBAR, LOCATED AT MINI MARKET, I.S.M ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR PANEER ROLLS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - MADRAS CAFE, LOCATED AT MAIN ROAD, JHARIA - (FAMOUS FOR DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - GOLI, LOCATED AT CITY CENTER - (FAMOUS FOR VADA PAAV)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - GUP SIP &amp; COFFEE, LOCATED AT NEAR P.M.C.H. GATE NO. 2, KUSUM VIHAR, MURLI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR ROLLS, NOODLES AND PASTA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>8 - FAST FOOD CENTER, LOCATED AT KOYLA NAGAR COLONY, KUSUM VIHAR - (FAMOUS FOR EGG ROLL)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>9 - GOKUL SWEETS, LOCATED AT MAIN ROAD, JHARIA - (FAMOUS FOR DESI GHEE LADOO)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>10 - PUNJAB SWEETS, LOCATED IN DHANBAD - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA AND RASMALAI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>11 - MADHULIKA SWEETS, LOCATED AT SHANTI BHAWAN, BANKMORE, JHARIA ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR KAJUBARFI AND LADOO)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>12 - MAA KALI SWEETS, LOCATED AT NILANCHAL MORE, NEAR BIG BAZAR, SARAIDHELA - (FAMOUS FOR GULAB JAMUN)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(205, 14, 31, 733, 'Assam', 'INDIA', 'DIBRUGARH', 'bihu-169920_640.jpg', 'bihu-169920_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">A major city in the north eastern region of India in line with cities like Guwahati and Bhubaneswar, Dibrugarh is the emerging communication and industrial hub of North East India. Deriving its name from the word Dibrumukha, the name of the river Dibru with the word mukh meaning mouth, Dibrugarh, is a city and is the headquarters of the Dibrugarh district in the state of Assam. Dibrugarh is also one of the two main cities in the state of Assam to receive urban development aid from the Asian Development Bank and is the nerve centre of industry, communication and healthcare of the upper Assam region. The city of Dibrugarh is emerging as a popular destination for business and leisure trips for tourists from India and abroad. This city is loaded with nature and culture, and is the destination to unwind tourists. Dibrugarh is located 439 kms east of Guwahati, divided by Buridihing, a tributary of Brahmaputra, divides the district from east to west. Buridihing flows through Naharkatia and Khowang, and at a later stage in its course, Buridihing acts as a divider between Dibrugarh and Sivasagar districts. This beautiful city is the gateway to the three tea producing districts of Tinsukia, Dibrugarh, and Sivasagar. These three areas account for approximately 50 percent of India&#39;s Assam tea crop, and this gives Dibrugarh its rightly earned sobriquet as the Tea City of India. Oil and timber are the other two big industries in and around Dibrugarh.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There is a variety of accommodation options available for the different types of tourists coming here. Ranging from Luxury Hotels, Guest Houses, Resorts, Service Apartments, all the way to nature camps by the river can be found. Fitting all budget types the tariffs here range from INR 500 to Rs.3500/.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Dibrugarh has a fully-functional airport and is well connected to the rest of the country. Daily direct flights to Kolkata, Delhi and Guwahati are available from the Dibrugarh airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail</strong> - Dibrugarh is the easternmost railway station of the country. This is an important railway station that connects the inner Northeast region to the rest of the country. Dibrugarh has two railway stations the Dibrugarh Town Station is the first railway station in the region and the newly constructed Dibrugarh station.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- The National Highway 37 connects Dibrugarh to the rest of the country. Travelling on road can be a thrilling experience thanks to the picturesque scenery all around. Regular buses are available from Guwahati to Dibrugarh. Daily buses are also available from Kohima to Dibrugarh. The Dibrugarh route also serves as a gateway to Arunachal Pradesh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Rickshaws are, by far, the best modes of intercity transport, which are easily available and that too at very low rates. Tourists can get auto as well as cycle rickshaws within the cities, from which they can choose one depending upon the distance to be covered as well as the budget in hand. The city bus that covers the whole region, is also a popular choice, though usually operates only in the day time. There are taxi services as well.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - DIBRUGARH - {FAMOUS FOR MASOR JOOL (FISH CURRIES MADE OF ROU, ILLISH OR CHITOL) ; &nbsp;PITIKA IS A DISH made FROM POTATO AND GARNISHED WITH CHILLIES, MUSTARD OIL AND ONION}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - MB&#39;S SWEETS &amp; SNACKS, LOCATED IN BABULAL PODDAR PATH, JALUKPARA - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - CHAWLA DILLIVALA, LOCATED IN KC GOGOI PATH, BORPUKHURIPAR, KHALIAMARI - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;CHICKEN BIRYANI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - MAMBOOZ DHABA, LOCATED IN NATIONAL HIGHWAY 37, NEAR M P JALAN PETROL PUMP, AMOLAPATTY - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN BUTTER MASALA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n5 - THE LUNCH BOX, FAST FOOD JOINT, LOCATED IN CONVOY ROAD, BOIRAGIMOTH - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN PULAO)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(206, 14, 31, 1657, 'Chhattisgarh', 'INDIA', 'DURG / BHILAI', 'architecture-1639990_640.jpg', 'architecture-1639990_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Durg city located in the Southwestern part of the Chhattisgarh is nestled amongst the majestic hills on the Southwest and Northwest sides. One of the most visited &amp; popular tourist destinations of Chattisgarh state it offers something for everyone. Apart from being one of the important cities of Chhattisgarh, Durg is also known to be a major industrial and agricultural centre. Located on the eastern banks of River Seonath also known as River Shivnath, Durg is the third largest city of Chhattisgarh. Durg is a heavily populated city and is rich in mineral resources. This district is situated to the south of the Upper Sheonath Mahanadi valley. Durg can be separated into two main physiographic divisions, the C.G Plain and the southern plateau. Sheonath, being the main River of the Durg District, is the main tributary of the Mahanadi River. The Sheonath River has a total length of 345 kms and has a tributary named the Tandula River. Durg also has another River knows as the Kharkhara. History states that the district of Durg was earlier a part of the &lsquo;Dakshina&rsquo; or the &lsquo;Kosala&rsquo; Rule. There is also evidence of the Ashoka Rule followed by the Marathas and then the British. Later on, during 1906, Durg was separated into a district. The city is mainly known for Bhilai Steel Plant (SAIL), one of the largest steel plants in India.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>City has range of accomodation options with limited facilites available accordingly.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- The closest airport to Durg is the Raipur Airport, which is at a distance of 54 kms. This airport connects to major cities like Delhi, Mumbai, Nagpur, Kolkata, Bhubneshwar, Chennai, Ranchi and Vishakapatnam.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail </strong>- The Durg Railway Station is situated on the Mumbai Howrah main line and it is 1101 kms away from Mumbai and 867 kms away from Howrah.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- The district of Durg is directly connected to Nagpur and Raipur. Durg is a well developed township connected to many neighbouring cities as well as stated with a well maintained network of roads. Several private as well as state owned buses run on regular basis to other major cities of the state.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Visitors can use taxis, tempos and autos to get around Durg. The steel city of Bhilai offers several ways of commuting within and around the city. Buses are the cheapest way of transportation while taxi tends to be the most convenient for tourists in the city. One can also hire a private vehicle to drive them about the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - TRIPTI RESTAURANT &amp; SWEETS HOME, LOCATED AT BEHIND LIC OFFICE, PADMANABHPUR - (FAMOUS FOR DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - JAIN CHAT CENTER, LOCATED AT &nbsp;PADMANABHPUR&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;- (FAMOUS FOR PANIPURI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - MADHURAM SWEETS, LOCATED AT CIVIC CENTER AREA, SECTOR 5, BHILAI - (FAMOUS FOR KAJU KATLI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - ANSARI, LOCATED AT DAKSHIN GANGOTRI, SUPELA, BHILA - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;BRIYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - JALARAM SWEETS, LOCATED AT KELABADI - (FAMOUS FOR DAHI KACHORI, DHOKLA AND LASSI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - NEW CALCUTTA SWEETS, LOCATED AT BORSI UTAI ROAD, BORSI COLONY, BORSI - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA WITH CHUTNEY)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(207, 14, 31, 739, 'Haryana', 'INDIA', 'FARIDABAD', 'india-1562386_1920.jpg', 'india-1562386_640.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Faridabad was founded in 1607 AD by Sheikh Farid, treasurer of Jahangir, with the object of protecting the highway, which passed through the town. Shaikh Farid built a fort, a tank and a mosque, which are now in ruins. Later, it became the headquarters of a pargana, which was held in jagir by the Ballabgarh ruler. Faridabad became 12th district of Haryana state on 15th August, 1979. Faridabad is the biggest city in the state of Haryana. It is ranks amongst the leading industrial hubs making a fat contribution to the state&rsquo;s revenue. Though the city is not as ancient as some of the major cities in Haryana, it has its share in history. The city of Faridabad named after its founder Baba Farid is the second largest city of Haryana. A fort, mosque and a tank was built by him, the ruins of which are still visible. The geographical location of Faridabad is important as it is surrounded by Delhi, Gurgaon and parts of Uttar Pradesh. It is located on the plains of the river Yamuna. It is situated 25 kms away from Delhi. Faridabad is an industrial hub and is a large producer of many industrial products. The climate of Faridabad is semiarid, hot and dry except in the monsoon season. However, the humidity level remains high during monsoons. During the non monsoon months, thunder storms and western disturbances are experienced occasionally.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Faridabad provides its guests with numerous hotels and guest houses falling under different tariff ranges. One can easily find hotels that best suit your budget, needs and convenience. Finding a place to stay will never be a problem in Faridabad.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air </strong>- The city is served by Indira Gandhi International airport, which is at a distance of 40 kms from the heart of the city with separate domestic and international terminals. Daily flights ply to all major cities of India and abroad.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail</strong> - There are three railway stations namely Faridabad, Ballabgarh and New Faridabad. Local trains are also available between Delhi and Faridabad.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road </strong>- It is well connected with roads as National Highway 2 passes through the region. Roadways services of Haryana and neighbouring states like Delhi Transport Corporation, Uttar Pradesh Transport Department, Madhya Pradesh Transport Department, etc. are easily accessible.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Travelling within the city is convenient. To travel short distances one can take cycle rickshaws or auto rickshaws. While for further locations there are bus services, autos and radio taxis which could be booked through phone calls or internet.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SHREE RATHNAM, LOCATED AT SCO NO.21, GROUND FLOOR, HUDA MARKET, NEAR ASHIRWAD RESTAURANT - (FAMOUS FOR SOUTH INDIAN FOOD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - MORE THAN PARANTHAS, LOCATED AT CROWN PLAZA MALL, MATHURA ROAD, SECTOR 15A - (FAMOUS FOR PARATHA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - SANJHA CHULHA, LOCATED AT 12, PART 2 MARKET, SECTOR 19 - (FAMOUS FOR PANNER, MUSHROOMS, KOFTA AND DAL)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - BREW N BARREL, LOCATED AT LEVEL-II, PARSVNATH CITY MALL, DELHI MATHURA ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR BIRYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - BALAJI SWEETS &amp; RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT 51-52, SECTOR 28 MARKET, SECTOR 28 - (FAMOUS FOR DAL MAKHANI AND JEERA &nbsp;AALOO)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - PUNJABI NATURE, LOCATED AT 167, B.K.KC ROAD, NEW INDUSTRIAL TOWNSHIP 5 - (FAMOUS FOR CHILLY CHICKEN AND DAL MAKHANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - CHARDI KALA,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT SHOP NO 129, HOUSING BOARD COLONY, SECTOR 10 - (FAMOUS FOR AALOO(PATATO) PARATHA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>8 - CAFE BOGCHI,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT SCF 39, FIRST FLOOR, ABOVE AXIS BANK, SECTOR 15 - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA, PASTA &nbsp;AND JUICES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>9 - HOT &amp; TASTY CHINESE FOOD, LOCATED AT SHOP NO.18, DLF MARKET, SECTOR 11 - (FAMOUS FOR CHILLI-POTATO)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>10 - CHACHA GYAN KA DHABA, LOCATED AT FAWDA CHOWK, SHAHID BHAGAT SINGH MARG, NEW INDUSTRIAL TWP 1, NEW INDUSTRIAL TOWN - (FAMOUS FOR MUTTON CURRY)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n11 - TRIPLE SEVEN, LOCATED AT TRIPLE CHOWK, 7, TIGAON RD, BALRAMGARH - (FAMOUS FOR SHAHI PANEER AND LACHA PRATHA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n12 - GO FOODIEZZ, LOCATED AT 3 D- 57 B.P E.S.I CHOWK N.I.T - (FAMOUS FOR SANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>13 - MOMO CHA, LOCATED AT J121, 9-10 DIVIDING RD, J BLOCK, SECTOR 10 HBC - (FAMOUS FOR MOMOS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>14 - AL BAKE, LOCATED AT SCF 58, GROUND FLOOR, MAIN MARKET, SECTOR 15, OPP. COMMUNITY CENTRE - (FAMOUS FOR SHAWARMA ROLLS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>15 - STAR CRUST, LOCATED AT SHOP NO. 2597, SECTOR 7A - (FAMOUS FOR CHILLY POTATO, AND COLD COFFEE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>16 - CHAWLA DILLIVALA, LOCATED AT MAIN BANDH RD, GREENFIELD COLONY BLOCK B, POCKET A, SANJAY GANDHI MEMORIAL NAGAR, NEW INDUSTRIAL TOWN - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN FRIED RICE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>17 - SOHAN SWEETS, LOCATED AT SHOP NO 115/17, 114, CHOUDHARY CHARAN SINGH MARG, SECTOR 17 - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSAS, KACHORI ALOO PURI, GULAB JAMUN AND JALEBI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>18 - MINI SWEET CORNER,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT SHOP NO. 17-18, MAIN MARKET, SECTOR 22 - (FAMOUS FOR CHHOLE BHTURE AND LASSI)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(208, 14, 31, 1653, 'Uttarakhand', 'INDIA', 'HARIDWAR', 'haridwar-687346_640.jpg', 'haridwar-687346_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Haridwar (or Hardwar) literally meaning &#39;The Gateway to the Gods&#39;, is an important pilgrimage centre, situated in the beautiful hill state of Uttarakhand. This holy city is one of the &lsquo;sapta-puris&rsquo; i.e. the seven holy cities of India. In addition, this place is the gateway to three other pilgrimage centres of Uttarakhand namely Rishikesh, Kedarnath, and Badrinath. The city of Haridwar is also known as Mayapuri, Kapila, Mokshadwar, and Gangadwar and finds mention in various ancient Hindu epics. The history of this sacred place dates back to the era of the illustrious King Vikramaditya. The destination is known for its world famous religious centres and tourist attractions. Most of the pilgrim spots here are situated on the banks of the holy Ganges River. The most important and pious site here is Har-ki-Pauri, which is popularly called Brahm Kund. This is the point from where the River Ganges exits the mountains and enters the plains. There are footprints on the ghats that are believed to be of the Hindu Lord Vishnu.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Visitors can choose from 5 stars to luxury hotels in Haridwar. There are also numerous guest houses in the city. Besides, one can also put up in a Dharamshala for a flavour of pilgrim travel.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air -</strong> The closest airbase to Haridwar is the Jolly Grant Airport in Dehradun, which is situated at a distance of around 34 kms from the destination. Flights to New Delhi are available from this airport on a daily basis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail </strong>- Haridwar has its own railway station, which is connected to important Indian cities. It is located just a kilometre away from the city centre.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- The place is well linked to other parts of the country by state and private operated buses. Various deluxe tourist buses frequently ply for Haridwar from New Delhi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Numerous buses, taxis and auto-rickshaws ply across the city. One can also take the local train that connects most of the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - BHGWATI, 10 MINS WALKING FROM LAL TARAO BRIDGE TOWARDS HAR KI PAURI - (FAMOUS FOR CHOLE BHATURE)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - MOHAN PURI WALA, ON GATE OF HAR KI PAURI - (FAMOUS FOR PURI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - SINDH DUGDH BHANDAR - (FAMOUS FOR MULTI CUSINE &amp; DESERTS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - AHAAR RESTAURANT, ON RLY STATION - (FAMOUS FOR PUNJABI CUSINE)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n5 - BESTEE RESTAURANT - (FAMOUS FOR VARIETY OF SHAKES)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n6 - BRIJ MATHURA WALA - (FAMOUS FOR VARIETY OF SWEETS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n7 - PANDIT POORI WALA, AT BARA BAZAR - (FAMOUS FOR POORI)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(209, 14, 31, 741, 'Jharkhand', 'INDIA', 'HAZARIBAGH', 'light-1604783_640.jpg', 'light-1604783_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Hazaribagh, as its name suggests, is a land of flora and fauna. The name Hazaribagh means a thousand gardens and the city lives up to its name. Situated at an altitude of 2019 feet above sea level, the city is a well known health resort. It has excellent climate and scenic beauties all around it in the midst of dense forest which is quite rich in flora and fauna. The Hazaribagh plateau has on its eastern margin, Parasnath the highest hill in the Bihar, rising to a height of 4480 feet. The loftiness here is of another order. According to the Jain tradition, no less than 23 out of 24 Tirthankars including Parsvantha are believed to have attained salvation in the Sammetasikhara of the Parasnath hills. The hill seems to have been an abode of Jains. The Prasvantha, 23rd Tirthankar was very popular among tribal population of Chotanagpur. He is identified by the snake king Dharanendra, whose many hoods protect the meditating Tirthankar. Both the Swetamber and Digamber Jains have many beautiful temples here on the hills. Located in the Chhota Nagpur plateau, 93 kms away from Ranchi, Hazaribagh is a beautiful place with dense forests and natural formations including rock formations and lakes. The forests in Hazaribagh are mostly unexplored and are in its best and purest form with full of greenery.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Hazaribagh has quite sufficient number of lodges and hotels to sleep or stay in. Tourists can choose according to their budget or needs. The hotels are clean and have average services. In a small town like Hazaribagh it is the best availability.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By air </strong>- The nearest airport is in Ranchi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By rail </strong>- Kodarma is the nearest railway station. Many trains are available to reach the destination.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By road</strong> - As it is located on NH33, transportation is not a problem. Moreover, many direct buses are available from all major cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local transport </strong>- Conveyance availability is quite easy in Hazaribagh. There are taxis, buses, auto rickshaws and cycle rickshaws which could be easily hired to commute within the city. However being a hilly area there are times when the journey isn&#39;t much comfortable and is tiring.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - HAZARIBAGH - {FAMOUS FOR DHUSKA IS A SNACK MADE FROM MASHED RICE AND PULSES ; CHARPA IS A SNACK MADE FROM MASHED RICE FRIED AND THEN MIXED WITH SPICES AND VEGETABLES}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - ZAIKA RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT OPPOSITE DILKHUSH SWEETS, GURU GOBIND SINGH ROAD, NAWABGANJ - (FAMOUS FOR MANCHURIAN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - PRADIP CHAT, LOCATED AT MANGURA - (FAMOUS FOR GOLGAPPA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - PUNJABI RASOI, LOCATED AT PTC RD, MATWARI, NEAR GANDHI MAIDAN, HIRABAG - (FAMOUS FOR KAWAB AND CHICKEN CHILLY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - SWAAD-THE BEST TASTE IN TOWN, LOCATED AT SURESH COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR RASOGULLA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - PANIPURI CENTRE, LOCATED AT HOLY CROSS ROAD, SURESH COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR PANIPURI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - SAMOSA CENTRE, LOCATED AT ATAL CHOWK, HIRABAG - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA WITH CHUTNEY AND ONIONS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '');
