(210, 14, 31, 751, 'Punjab', 'INDIA', 'HOSHIARPUR', 'wheat-fields-762221_640.jpg', 'wheat-fields-762221_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Hoshiarpur is a district of Punjab state in northern India. Hoshiarpur, one of the oldest districts of Punjab, is located in the North-east part of the Punjab state and shares common boundaries with Gurdaspur district in the north-west, Jalandhar and Kapurthala districts in Southwest, Kangra and Una districts of Himachal Pradesh in the Northeast. It falls into two nearly equal portions of hill and plain country. Its eastern face consists of the westward slope of the Solar Singhi Hills; parallel with that ridge, a line of lower heights belonging to the Siwalik Range traverses the district from south to north, while between the two chains stretches a valley of uneven width, known as the Jaswan Dun. Its upper portion is crossed by the Sohan torrent, while the Sutlej sweeps into its lower end through a break in the hills, and flows in a southerly direction until it turns the flank of the central range, and debouches westwards upon the plains. It is an old city of temples. It dates back to the Stone Age. Indo-Sanskrit studies and Brighushamita Astrology are important parts of the place. Colourful lacquers are also manufactured here. King George the V&rsquo;s coronation is depicted through the Sheesh Mahal. The Vedic Research Institute is a known place here. It is also known for Bhrigusamhita system of astrology as well as lacquer finished furniture manufacturing. The place also has an archaeological museum.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Punjab is the state known for its hospitality and same reflects in the hotel industry of Hoshiarpur. It is well known for warm hospitality and loving nature of locals. Being preferred location of tourism, there are many hotels, luxurious and semi luxurious established in every part of the city. Popular hotels in Hoshiarpur are located near bus stand and railway road. People coming to this city can find all categories of hoteliers who offer budget accommodations as well as luxurious stay. Even resorts are the excellent option to choose for stay in Hoshiarpur.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Hoshiarpur by Air</strong> - Hoshiarpur offers quite few options to the air travellers for reaching the city. The nearest airport for arriving in Hoshiarpur is Sahnewal Airport in Ludhiana. It is 78 kms from Hoshiarpur and connected to Delhi and Pathankot by daily flights.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Hoshiarpur by Train</strong> - Train is the good medium to reach Hoshiarpur in Punjab. Hoshiarpur possesses its own railway station which is connected to all parts of rail network through Jalandhar Junction or Dasuya railway station. Jalandhar city and Dasuya is approximately 40 kms away from Hoshiarpur and every major train has halt at this station.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Hoshiarpur by Road</strong> - Hoshiarpur is situated in the centralized location of the region. National Highway 70 passes through the city of Hoshiarpur which is also connected to state highways of Punjab. Tourist coming by private car could arrive directly to the city of Hoshiarpur by taking such fast highways to approach here.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Strategically, its position is vital and many major towns are placed in the vicinity of Hoshiarpur. Buses, taxis, tourist coach, prepaid cabs; rental cars are easily available to visit the tourist destinations around the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - KANDI PEHALWAN DI HATTI, LOCATED AT OPPOSITE OLD SABJI MANDI,JALANDHAR ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR DAHI BHALLA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - OHRI SWEET SHOP, LOCATED AT B 4/876, CHHATTA BAZAR, CHHATTA BAZA - (FAMOUS FOR LASSI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - OM PARKASH SWEET SHOP, LOCATED AT KRISHNA NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR IMATRI &nbsp;AND SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - CAFE GELATERIA, LOCATED AT PRAKASH TOWER, PHAGWARA ROAD, TULSI NAGAR, KAMALPUR - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - NEST SNACK, LOCATED AT OPPOSITE BUS STAND,LAXMI MARKET - (FAMOUS FOR CHOLE BHATURE)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(211, 14, 31, 751, 'Punjab', 'INDIA', 'JALANDHAR', 'shalamar-garden-1021933_640.jpg', 'shalamar-garden-1021933_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Jalandhar located 144 kms Northwest of Chandigarh, the state capital; it is also the city with the maximum percentage of non resident Indians. It is among the oldest surviving cities of the Punjab region. It is known for its sportsmen as well as its sports industry, its steel and iron re-rolling mills, rubber goods, electric goods, automobile parts and sewing machine factories and handloom products. Jalandhar is an ancient city that has a rich history. It is named after Jalandhara a demon king, mentioned in the Puranas and the Mahabharata. Jalandhar in Hindi means &lsquo;an area that lies under water&rsquo;, and as per folklore the city derived this name owing to its geographical location between two rivers Beas and Sutlej. Post independence, the city served as the capital of Punjab until 1953, when Chandigarh acquired this status. The city&rsquo;s rich culture and tradition along with a number of tourist attractions make Jalandhar tourism popular among travellers.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Choosing hotels in Jalandhar is a not &not;so &not;easy task as you are given numerous options. Be it a simple accommodation or a luxury sojourn, Jalandhar has everything to offer. Hotels and Resorts are easily available. Most of the low budget hotels are situated near the bus and railway station while mid budget ones are all over the city. So, treat yourself with the luxury and comfort that one deserves the most on a trip.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport to Jalandhar is the Raja Sansi Airport in Amritsar, which is around 90 kms away from the city. Tourists reaching Amritsar by air can book a cab at the airport to travel to Jalandhar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail </strong>- Jalandhar City Railway Station lies on the Delhi Amritsar railway line. A number of trains like Shatabdi and Jammu Mail operate regularly between Delhi and Jalandhar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road </strong>- Jalandhar is connected to all major cities of Punjab and other nearby states by a network of buses. Tourists can choose from different types of buses as per their preference, such as Volvo, Deluxe and Semi Deluxe.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Tourist attractions of Jalandhar can be accessed using private taxis, auto-rickshaws, cycle-rickshaws and local buses. Adequate tourist information in hand can help visitors to explore the places better.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - LUCKY VAISHNO DHABA, LOCATED AT G T ROAD JALANDHAR PHAGWARA HIGHWAY - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;DAL MAKHANI AND ALOO PARATHA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - HAVELI, LOCATED AT PHAGWARA HIGHWAY, GT ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR LASSI AND MAKKI DI ROTI TE SARSO DA SAAG)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - FOOD BAZAR, LOCATED AT AT MADAN FLOUR MILLS COMPOUND, LADOWALI ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;SHAKES AND ICE CREAM)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - DASHMESH VAISHNO DHABA, LOCATED AT HOSHIARPUR ROAD RAMA MANDI - (FAMOUS FOR DALMALKHNI,PANEER BURJI AND ALOO GOBHI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - LOVELY SWEETS, LOCATED AT JALANDHAR CANTT MARKET - (FAMOUS FOR RASMALAI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n6 - KURRY&#39;S &amp; KABAB, LOCATED AT 113, MAHAVIR MARG, OPP. BROILER MASTER, ADARSH NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR PANEER &nbsp;MAKHANI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n7 - GIANI KHARORE WALA, LOCATED AT &nbsp;MILAP CHOWK,NEAR CITY VIEW HOTEL - (FAMOUS FOR MUTTON TIKKA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>8 - CHHABRA SWEETS &amp; DELIGHTS, LOCATED AT ADJOINING S.B.I., NAKODAR ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA AND KULCHE CHOLE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>9 - SUPER CREMICA SWEETS, LOCATED AT CANNAUGHT CIRCUS, OPPOSITE GOVT GIRLS SEN SECTOR,, INDUSTRIAL AREA - (FAMOUS FOR RASMALAI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>10 - DHAN GURU RAM DASS SWEETS, LOCATED AT LADOWALI ROAD, NEAR BHAGAT SINGH CHOWK, CHAHAR BAGH, BAJWA COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR MILK CAKE)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(212, 14, 31, 741, 'Jharkhand', 'INDIA', 'JAMSHEDPUR', 'person-690245_640.jpg', 'person-690245_1280.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The largest city in Jharkhand, Jamshedpur is an appealing destination with its aesthetically planned infrastructure and landscape. Jamshedpur is the quintessential example of the boon of industrialization in a developing nation. It is the largest city in Jharkhand and is majorly maintained by the Tata Industries. The prosperity of the city and its people is clearly reflected in the sparkle of industry and infrastructure. Jamshedpur, also known as the Industrial City of India was founded by the late Jamshedji Nusserwanji Tata. It is the most populous city in the state of Jharkhand and popularly known as the Steel City or Tatanagar. Jamshedpur is the headquarters of East Singhbhum district of Jharkhand and is the third largest city in East India after Kolkata and Patna. It is home to one of the largest industrial zones of India known as Adityapur which boasts of more than 1,000 small and medium scale industries.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Owing to the thriving industrial development of the city, Jamshedpur has a lot of visitors all year round. So whether here for business or leisure, choose the hotel as per requirements and preferences and enjoy the stay. Jamshedpur offers a lot of hotels in a low range budget and there are several other options for the travellers on a mid-range budget. Luxury hotels, 3 star hotels, 2 star hotels and even cheap accommodation are available in the city.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Jamshedpur has a small airport called as Sonari Airport and is primarily used for bringing in chartered planes of Tata Group. The nearest commercial airports are Kolkata and Ranchi which is at a distance of around 289 kms and 130 kms respectively.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail -</strong> Jamshedpur, also known as Tatanagar Railway Station is the most important junction of the state and is the second busiest station of South Eastern Railway after Howrah. The city is well connected to all the major cities of India like Kolkata, Mumbai, Delhi, Ahmedabad, Bangalore, Nagpur, Bhubaneshwar and Pune. The other important stations are Adityapur, Gamharia, Kandra, Govindpur and Salgajhari.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road -</strong> Jamshedpur is connected to other parts of India by National and State Highways. The major highways are National Highway 33 which connects to Mumbai and Delhi. The National Highway 6 connects to Kharagpur and Kolkata.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- One can travel around in auto-rickshaws, minibuses or hired cabs. Taking a minibus is the most economical option. &nbsp;It is a popular mode of transport among commuters.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - DELHI DARBAR, LOCATED AT SARKAR BUILDING, SAKCHI - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN BIRIYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - FAKIRA CHANACHUR, LOCATED AT MAIN ROAD, TRAFFIC SIGNAL LIGHT, NEAR KAMANI CENTRE - (FAMOUS FOR ROASTED LENTIL AND PEANUTS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - TAMBI&rsquo;S, LOCATED AT NEAR THE PETROL PUMP, CH AREA - (FAMOUS FOR DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - BHATIA MILK SHAKE, LOCATED AT FRUIT MARKET BISTUPUR, NEAR CONFIDENCE MOBILE SHOP - (FAMOUS FOR VARITIES OF MILKSHAKES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - HARI KA GOLGAPPA, LOCATED AT 26 ROAD, DURGA PUJA MAIDAN, TELCO COLONY - {FAMOUS FOR GOLGAPPAS(PANI PURI)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - BAUWAJI, LOCATED AT BEHIND PETROL PUMP, NORTHERN TOWN T.O.P., C.H. AREA - {FAMOUS FOR CHAI AND SINGADA(SAMOSA)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - BHOLA MAHARAJ, LOCATED AT 111, BHOLA MAHARAJ LANE, SAKCH - (FAMOUS FOR MOTICHOOR LADDU, BALUSHAHI, CHANDRAKALA, SANTRA KADAM AND MOTIPAK)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>8 - GUPTA KI MITHAIYAN, LOCATED AT 143, LAL BUILDING, SAKCHI BAZAAR - (FAMOUS FOR RABRI AND RASMALAI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>9 - LAKHI ROLLS, LOCATED AT NEAR BASANT TALKIES, SAKCHI - (FAMOUS FOR EGG ROLL, CHOWMEIN AND CHILLI CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>10 - MANOHAR CHAT, LOCATED AT NEAR BASANT TALKIES - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;SAMBHAR VADA AND MIX CHAT)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>11 - GOLI, LOCATED AT NEXT TO LAKHI ROLLS, OPPOSITE BASANT TALKIES, SAKCHI - (FAMOUS FOR COLA, ORANGE OR NIMBU SODA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>12 - BHATIA, LOCATED AT PURANI JALEBI DUKAN, NO.11 REFUGEE MARKET, SAKCHI - (FAMOUS FOR JALEBI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>13 - MAA TARINI/REGAL COLD DRINK, LOCATED AT NEXT TO PETROL PUMP, REGAL MAIDAN, BISTUPUR - (FAMOUS FOR MOCKTAILS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>14 - CALCUTTA BAKERY, LOCATED AT DHATKIDIH MARKET AREA - (FAMOUS FOR PASTRIES, BISCUITS, PATTIES)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n15 - SURENDER KEWAT, LOCATED AT BUS STAND, KALIMATI ROAD, NEAR GURDWARA, SAKCHI GOLCHAKKAR - (FAMOUS FOR LITTI CHOKHA WITH CHUTNEY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>16 - NABJIBAN, LOCATED AT SAKCHI BAZAAR - (FAMOUS FOR KULFI FALOODA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n17 - BFC (BALBIR FRIED CHICKEN), LOCATED AT OPPOSITE BASANT TALKIES, SAKCHI - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN CHAANP AND CHICKEN PAKODA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>18 - CAFE REGAL, LOCATED AT 2ND FLOOR, 35 BHARUCHA MANSION, BISTUPUR - (FAMOUS FOR COLD COFFEE (RS 130), CHICKEN PASTA IN WHITE SAUCE)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n19 - THE MADRASI HOTEL, LOCATED AT J ROAD, BISTUPUR - (FAMOUS FOR DOSA, GHEE FRIED IDLI AND COFFEE)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n20 - SHUKLA SWEETS, LOCATED AT AZAD MARKET - (FAMOUS FOR LADDUS, RASMALAI, RASOGOLLA, GULABJAMUN, SANDESH)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>21 - JUNCTION, LOCATED AT MILLENIUM TOWERS, SOUTH PARK, BISTUPUR - (FAMOUS FOR KABAB)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>22 - GANPATI FAMILY RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT SHERE-E-PUNJAB CHOWK, ADITYAPUR - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN BUTTER MASALA WITH &nbsp;BUTTER NAAN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>23 - NILESH FAST FOOD CORNER, LOCATED AT RIVER VIEW, PRAKASH NAGAR, GHORABANDHA - (FAMOUS FOR CHOWMIEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>24 - DADDY&#39;S KITCHEN,LOCATED AT INNER CIRCLE ROAD, CONTRACTORS AREA, BISTUPUR - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN BIRYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>25 - ANAND RAO, LOCATED AT FRONT OF TATA WORKS NEAR KAGALNAGAR PARK, SONARI - (FAMOUS FOR DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>26 - SAURAV FAST FOOD, LOCATED AT TATA KANDRA ROAD, ADITYAPUR BASTI - (FAMOUS FOR EGG ROLLS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>27 - SAGAR SWEET, LOCATED AT DIAGONAL ROAD, BISTUPUR - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>28 - SWEET MART, LOCATED AT SHOP NO. 105, KADMA MARKET - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA CHAT)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>29 - SALIGRAM SWEETS, LOCATED AT HOUSING COLONY, ADITYAPUR - (FAMOUS FOR RASOGULLA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>30 - GOPALA SWEETS, LOCATED AT ADITYAPUR STATION ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA AND KACHORI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n31 - PRADEEP SWEETS &amp; SNACKS, LOCATED AT INDUSTRIAL AREA, ADITYAPUR - (FAMOUS FOR ALOO PARATHA AND FRIED RICE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>32 - MAA LAXMI SWEETS, LOCATED AT &nbsp;POST OFFICE ROAD, MANGO - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA AND JALEBI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>33 - ASHA MISHTANN BHANDAR, LOCATED AT KRISHNA COMPLEX, ROAD NO.2 , SUNDAY MARKET, BIRSA NAGAR (NEAR OLD POST OFFICE) - (FAMOUS FOR KAJU KATLI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>34 - RASRAJ BHOG, LOCATED AT NEAR BAJRONG CHOWK, BANIDIH BASTI, BARIDIH - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;RASGULLA)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(213, 14, 31, 738, 'Gujrat', 'INDIA', 'JUNAGADH', 'architectural-1930982_640.jpg', 'architectural-1930982_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Being the capital of Junagadh Princely State once, the town shines with historical significance with many historical monuments to see. Very few places in Gujarat have the diversity that Junagadh offers. Located at the foothills of the Girnar range, Junagadh got its name because of Uparkot, a fort built by Chandra Gupta Maurya during 320 BC. &ldquo;Old Fort&rdquo; as the word Junagadh means the fort at the main centre of the city. Junagadh is quite ancient as it existed during the reigns of Chandra Gupta Maurya and King Ashoka. Inscriptions dating back to the era of the Saka Ruler Mahakshatrap Rudradaman I can also be found. During Mohammad Bahadur Khanji I, the present city of Junagadh was founded. He laid the foundation of the &ldquo;Babi Dynasty&rdquo; that ruled the place till the British declared it as a Princely state and Junagadh opted to accede India during the partition. Junagadh has diverse weather conditions throughout the year. The climate of Junagadh is characterized by very hot summers and chilly winters. The city also enjoys a soothing effect on the weather due to the influence of the Arabian Sea and the Gulf of Cambay.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are various hotels in this tourist hot-spot. There are plenty of standard hotels and resorts with all sorts of amenities to present the visitors an experience of a lifetime. There are luxury hotels, Premium hotels and also Budget hotels in Junagadh.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest airport is located at Keshod and Porbandar which are about 40 and 113 kms respectively.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail </strong>- Junagadh has a Railway Station. Trains are available to places with the state and to cities in nearby states. The railway station is located on the Ahmedabad-Junagadh and Rajkot-Junagadh line.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road </strong>- Junagadh is connected with various major cities in Gujarat like Rajkot, Porbandar and Ahmedabad. Buses are available to the city from local destination in the state like Rajkot and from cities in Maharashtra.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Tourists can access the whole town on auto rickshaws or by using taxis. The Local bus network is efficient as well.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(214, 14, 31, 743, 'Kerala', 'INDIA', 'KALADY', 'leaf-1186158_640.jpg', 'leaf-1186158_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kalady is a village located near the Periyar River. The village is geographically located in Ernakulum, Kerala. It is the birthplace of Adishankara, the great saint who established the doctrine of Non dualism or Advaita Vedanta School of the Hindu philosophy. &nbsp;It is a very popular destination for pilgrims from all over India specially the followers of Adishankara. A temple for Adishankara was built in the year 1910. Kalady means footprint, the village was formerly known as Sasalam. The centenary of Kalady was also celebrated and widely covered by the media in the year 2010. This town has legendary beginnings with stories about Adi Shankara and his mother. The Periyar Rriver was earlier known as the &#39;Purna&#39; River. The best season to visit this place is from August to March when the temperatures are cooler.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kalady offers a wide range of accommodation from tourist huts to budget hotels and from 5-star holes and home stays to government guest houses.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest Airport to Kalady is the Kochi Airport at a distance of 7 kms. This airport is connected to all the major airports in India and many cities abroad.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail </strong>- The nearest railway station is in Aluva which is 18 kms from Kalady, and is connected to all the major Indian cities like Chennai, Bangalore, Delhi and Mumbai. Trains from all major cities have a stopover here.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Bus services are also available from Kerala to Kalady. The Kerala State Road Transport Corporation operates many buses which commute to and fro Kalady. The availability Private buses also make travelling by road a happy experience. The Super Deluxe buses connect Kalady to other major south Indian cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Private taxis and cabs are available at a cheaper rate. Local bus services are the cheapest mode to communicate around the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - ROYAL FOOD COURT, LOCATED AT SH 1, CHENGAL - (FAMOUS FOR SHAKES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - HOTEL SARAVANA BHAVAN, LOCATED AT THRISSUR ROAD, ANGAMALY - (FAMOUS FOR PANEER MASALA DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(215, 14, 31, 1652, 'Himachal Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'KANGRA', 'waterfall-1031597_6403.jpg', 'waterfall-1031597_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kangra is a tourist destination located at the meeting point of the Manjhi and Bener streams in Himachal Pradesh. Nestled in Kangra Valley between Dhauladhar Range and Shivalik Range, this city overlooks the Banganga stream. It is also commonly known as Dev Bhumi, which means the abode of the Gods. According to the Vedas, various non Aryan tribal communities resided here before the arrival of the Aryans. In the great Indian epic Mahabharata, Kangra is referred to as the Trigarta Kingdom. The city of Kangra came under the rule of the Muslims after it was invaded by Mohammed of Ghazni in the 10th century. Thereafter, it came under the rule of the Katoch Dynasty, the oldest surviving dynasty. After the conclusion of the first Anglo Sikh War, Kangra was taken over by the British. In 1846, it became a district of Colonial India. Following the partition of the country in 1947, it became a part of Punjab in 1947, but was transferred to Himachal Pradesh in 1966. Travellers can visit various exotic tourist destinations at Kangra, such as Kareri Lake, Bagalamukhi Temple, and Kaleshwar Mahadev Temple. The best time to visit the site is during the summer season, which starts in the month of March and continues till June. Travellers can also visit the place during monsoons as the climate remains favourable for outdoor activities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kangra has a huge variety of hotels and lodges to offer for the stay. If on a tighter budget, opt for lodge without second thoughts, for they will help save up for the longer journey in the district. If the budget is more flexible, there are plenty of options to choose from, from acclaimed hotels and 5 star resorts providing the best luxury experiences in the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - Gaggal Airport is the nearest air base, as it is located at a distance of 13 kms from Kangra. Jammu Airport and Sri Guru Ram Das Jee International Airport (Amritsar) are the other air bases in the vicinity of Kangra, located 200 kms and 208 kms away, respectively.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail </strong>- Pathankot Broad Gauge Railway Station is the nearest rail head, located at a distance of 90 kms from Kangra. Taxi service is available at nominal rates from this railway station and transports tourists to Kangra in 2 to 3 hours.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road </strong>- Travellers interested in exploring Kangra can also visit the destination by buses. Government as well as private buses ply between Kangra and major places like Dharamshala, Palampur, Pathankot, Jammu, Amritsar, and Chandigarh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport </strong>- All the intra city tours are possible only with a cab because of the steepness of the paths at places and the ease of travel as well. Make sure to book yours beforehand with a hefty bargain, or if travelling with own vehicle, make sure to have the tank full for the journey.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1- KANGRA - (FAMOUS FOR PINNI IS A DESERT MADE FROM WHEAT FLOUR, KHOYA (THICKENED MILK) AND DRY FRUITS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - YOYO EATING POINT MAIN BAZAR KANGRA, LOCATED AT MANDIR ROAD, NEW KANGRA - (FAMOUS FOR BURGERS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - SHARMA BAKERS &amp; FAST FOOD, LOCATED AT NATIONAL HIGHWAY 88, HARIPUR, NEW KANGRA - (FAMOUS FOR PASTA AND MOMOS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - KARTIK KRISH VAISHNO DHABA, LOCATED AT RANITAL, KANGRA, NH-88, SHIMLA KANGRA ROAD, KANGRA - (FAMOUS FOR PANEER PARANTHA AND CHILLY PARANTHA)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(216, 14, 31, 1655, 'Jammu & Kashmir', 'INDIA', 'KARGIL', 'mont-blanc-1602750_6401.jpg', 'mont-blanc-1602750_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Kargil, also known as the Land of Agas, is a district in the Ladakh region of Jammu &amp; Kashmir. The district derives its name from the fact that is primarily occupied by Shia Muslims. Situated at a distance of around 205 kms from Srinagar, Kargil is located in proximity to the Line of Control or LOC with Pakistan and looks onto the valley of Kashmir. The place was the centre for the Kargil War or Kargil Conflict that took place during 1999 between India and Pakistan. The word Kargil is a blend of two words, &lsquo;Khar&rsquo; meaning castle and &lsquo;rkil&rsquo; meaning centre. The term, therefore, means a place between castles, an apt name for the destination, which lies between the two countries of India and Pakistan. Kargil is popular for its monasteries, picturesque valleys, and small towns. The place has a few important tourist attractions and religious centres for Buddhists such as the Sani Monastery, the Mulbekh Monastery, and the Shargole Monastery. Kargil is located in Ladakh and is a usual stopover for people leading towards Leh or Padum.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">There are many options of lodges, guest houses or hotels. But they have basic amenities, and some of them may even be unkempt.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air </strong>- The Srinagar Airport is the nearest airport to Kargil, located at a distance of about 206 kms from the destination. It is well connected with important cities in India like New Delhi, Mumbai, Shimla, and Chandigarh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Rail</strong> - Jammu Tawi Railway Station is the closest rail link to Kargil located at a distance of about 540 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Road </strong>- Tourists can avail direct buses from Leh and Srinagar for Kargil. Buses for Srinagar are available from Jammu, Chandigarh, Delhi, Phalgan, and Leh. Tourists can also avail J&amp;K State Road Transport Corporation bus services from Jammu. Tourists can also opt for jeep, taxi and mini coaches.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- There are either bus services that run through the city or one can hire a personal or shared jeep for travelling. Parts of it can also be covered on foot.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(217, 14, 31, 733, 'Assam', 'INDIA', 'KAZIRANGA', 'esterhazy-palace-89510_640.jpg', 'esterhazy-palace-89510_1280.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Kaziranga National Park, a UNESCO World Heritage Site, is located in the Golaghat and Nagaon districts in the state of Assam. It was declared a Reserve Forest in 1905. The park consists of an area of 429.93 sq kms with a buffer area of 429.40 sq kms. Kaziranga has large bio reserves of tall elephant grass, marshland and dense tropical moist broad leaf forests. The park celebrated its centennial in 2005 after its establishment in 1905 as a Reserve Forest. The park is maintained by the Assam Forest Department and Wildlife Trust of India along with the International Fund for Animal Welfare who has set up rehabilitation centres for distressed animals. Every year, an Elephant Festival is organised at the park to create awareness about the protection and conservation of Asiatic elephants. Kaziranga National Park can be visited from November to April. Elephant safaris and Kaziranga Wildlife Tours can be availed at the park. Made unique with a vibrant, well preserved and sustained ecology this park has a very versatile bio diversity which makes Kaziranga National Park a very important and popular tourist destination. Apart from the wildlife, the park itself is immensely beautiful with water bodies and forests.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Rooms here are usually booked and even over booked during the peak holiday season between November and May. So it&rsquo;s best to make advance booking. Rooms start at Rs. 1000 in most places. There are good luxury hotels too. Fares go up to Rs. 5000/Night. Fares are subject to change depending on the season. During summer months, an air conditioned room is a necessity. There are all kinds of motels, hotels and resorts here. Good resorts are equipped with spas, bar, gift shop and other basics.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest functional airport to Kaziranga is in Jorhat, located about 82 kilometres from the national park. The Jorhat airport has regular flights to Guwahati and Kolkata. The nearest international airport is the Lokpriya Gopinath Bordoloi Airport at Guwahati.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Rail </strong>- Kaziranga does not have a train station, and the nearest station is Jorhat, at a distance of 77 kms from Kaziranga. The closest railhead is Guwahati.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Road </strong>- Roadways are the lifeline for Kaziranga National Park. The National Highway 37A connects Kaziranga to Guwahati and Upper Assam. Tezpur is about 80 kilometres from Kaziranga while the other nearby town in Jorhat. For tourists travelling to Kaziranga directly from Guwahati, there are several buses and vehicles that can be booked.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- One can opt for safari rides in the park in either jeeps or SUVs and this is the best way to get around the park. Elephant rides can be arranged and they have to be booked in advance as they are popular.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(218, 14, 31, 743, 'Kerala', 'INDIA', 'KOCHI', 'kochi-972838_640.jpg', 'kochi-972838_1280.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Situated on beach-side, Kochi is a bustling commercial port with a trading history that dates back to at least 600 years, and is till today the financial capital of Kerala. The city is marked by influences of Arabs, Dutch, Phoenicians, Portuguese, Chinese and the British city as well as that of the Indian rule of Chera Dynasty followed by rule of the Feudal Lords. A gaggle of islands inter-connected by ferries, this cosmopolitan town has upmarket stores, art galleries and some of the finest heritage accommodations. In a true vintage-meets-future fashion, pubs, restaurants, shopping hubs and futuristic stores crowd Ernakulum, Jew Town and Fort Kochi while palaces, beaches, temples and heritage sites marking their presence too. Kerala is known as, Gods Own Country, for its breath-taking beauty and the city of Kochi lies on the South West Coast overlooking the Arabian Sea. For centuries Kochi has been a gathering place for merchants and tourists from various nations and people who have been here from Arabs to the Portuguese and British have all left their legacy and cultural imprints behind. Today Kochi has emerged as one of the must see destinations places to visit in Kerala and the cultural and historical significance of Kochi offers variety of experiences in and around the tourist places in Kochi. Kochi is a well-established commercial port having a long history rooted back to the 13th century. Famous for giant fishnets, Portuguese houses and ancient mosques it came into being after its separation from the Kulashekhara Empire. The South Indian culture is totally reflected in the city formerly called Cochin. The port is busy with a number of fishermen and traders.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Fort Cochin has many hotels which are more European and American in style. Ernakulum City caters to all travellers. Willingdon Island hosts some of the city&#39;s most premium hotels. Backpackers and Budget Travellers can head to home-stays on Fort Cochin. Kochi welcomes every tourist with open arms. It has a lot to offer and draws visitors from countries across the globe. Kochi is the place to find perfect harmony among all the elements of nature. It is the finest place to spend some time and nap in some of India&#39;s finest home stays and heritage accommodations. There are some heritage hotels and resorts in Kochi which are operated by Kerala tourism. These hotels extend the warmth and excitement of traditional hospitality of Kochi.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Cochin International Airport in Nedumbassery is situated 25 kms from the main city of Kochi. The airport receives both national and well as international flights. Taxi services are easily available both within and outside the airport. The taxi service from the airport can be availed any time of the day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail </strong>- Kochi has two railway stations; the Ernakulum Junction and the Ernakulum Town. Ernakulum Junction is the South railway station, and the Ernakulum Town station is the North railway station. Both the stations are well connected with the rest of the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Kochi is well connected with the rest of the country. The city is an important place in the North-South Corridor. State buses from surrounding cities and neighbouring states can bring one comfortably to Kochi. Check out several transport companies and compare their prices before boarding a private bus since fares may vary.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water</strong> - A regular yacht service from sea port areas like Goa, Mumbai, Lakshadweep, Colombo and Male is available. The interconnecting scenic backwaters provide regular boat services from places like Kottayam, Kumarakom, and Alleppey to Kochi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- A number of buses, autos, taxis and boats ferry people around at all times of the day. Metro lines are also under construction.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - MENORAH (SEA FOOD),&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;IN KODER HOUSE, TOWER ROAD, PORT - (FAMOUS FOR JEWISH CUSINE)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - FORT HOUSE RESTAURANT, AT 26/A CALVATHI ROAD, FORT COCHIN - (FAMOUS FOR KERLA FRIED PRAWNS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - THE HISTORY, AT BRUNTON BOATYARD HOTEL, RIVER ROAD, FORT COCHIN - [FAMOUS FOR CHUTTULI MEEN I.E FRIED FISH COOKED IN SPICES (JEWIS DISH)]&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">4 - KAYEES, AT DURBAR HILL ROAD, MATTANCHERRY - (FAMOUS FOR BIRYANI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n5 - SHALA, AT PETER CELLI STREET, FORT KOCHIN - [FAMOUS FOR MALABAR PRAWN CURRY (LOCAL KERLAN CUSINE)]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n6 - TEAPOT CAFE - (FAMOUS FOR CHOCLATE CAKE &amp; IS LIKE A TEA MUSEUM)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n7 - MALBAR JUNCTION, AT &nbsp;PARADE ROAD, FORT COCHIN - (FAMOUS FOR CHOCLATE FILLED SAMOSA IN MANGO SAUCE)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n8 - ARCA NOVA RESTAURANT, AT CALAVATHY ROAD, FORT COCHI - (FAMOUS FOR KERAL-LATIN CHRISTIAN CUSINE)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n9 - DAL ROTI, AT NAIPER STREET &nbsp;FORT KOCHI - (FAMOUS FOR NORTH INDIAN DELIGHTS &amp; KATHI ROLLS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n10 - GINGER HOUSE RESTAURANT, AT JEW TOWN MANTANCHERRY - (FAMOUS FOR HISTORICAL DISHES)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(219, 14, 31, 1659, 'Manipur', 'INDIA', 'IMPHAL', 'sunset-343833_640.jpg', 'sunset-343833_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Imphal, the capital of Manipur is a tucked away small town in north east India. Imphal came to prominence during the Second World War when the Japanese entered India and waged war over the area. The Battle of Imphal and the Battle of Kohima is significantly mentioned in the history of Second World War as this was the first time the fierce Japanese troop was defeated in Asian soil. Many thought that the war would badly affect Imphal, but surprisingly the city rose up with new vigour and rebuilt itself from scratch. Imphal has a untouched charm surrounding its natural beauty, sceneries and landscapes as well as a significant history leaving hints of the past around the city. The lust green landscapes, beautiful surroundings, unexplored territories and undulating rivers of Imphal make for a great tourist destination. Imphal has a number of tourist destinations which include INA memorial, Manipur State museum, Kangla Fort, Langthabal, war cemeteries, Shri Govindjee temple as well as the Waithou and Loktal Lake. Manipur Zoological gardens and Keibul Lamjao National park are also places one might not want to miss.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Budget ranges of hotels are available here for the tourists.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Imphal Airport is located about 8 kilometres from the city and well connected by shuttle cabs and other means of public transport. There are direct flights from New Delhi, Kolkata, Guawahati, Aizwal, Bangalore and Silchar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail</strong> - There are no railway stations in and around Imphal. Dimapur is the nearest major railway station and located 208 kilometres from the town. Cabs for Imphal are easily available at the Dimapur Railway Station.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Visitors can reach Imphal by road from all major towns and cities in North East. It is 479 kilometres from Guwahati connected by NH 39 and NH 150. One can also reach this city via Dimapur which is located at a distance of 208 kilometres.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport -</strong> Auto rickshaws and taxis are the main mode of transport within the city. Certain streets can also be explored on foot.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - MELLOW THE CASUAL RESTO, LOCATED AT &nbsp;DM COLLEGE ROAD, THANGMEIBAND HIJAM LEIKAI - (FAMOUS FOR FRIED RICE AND BIRYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - ZAIKA HALAL RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT &nbsp;DEWLAHLAND, ADJACENT TO ISBT BUS STAND - (FAMOUS FOR KEBAB AND MUTTON CURRY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - CAFE CABANE, LOCATED AT &nbsp;KONJENG HAZARI LEIKAI, SAGOLBAND - (FAMOUS FOR FRIED RICE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - POLLITO&#39;S, LOCATED AT &nbsp;DM COLLEGE ROAD, KABRABAM LEIKAI, THANGMEIBAND HIJAM LEIKAI - (FAMOUS FOR FRIED CHICKEN AND BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - FOOD VILLA, LOCATED AT &nbsp;NAGAMAPAL ROAD, MAJORKHUL, THANGAL BAZAR - (FAMOUS FOR BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - A-TO-Z FAST FOOD, LOCATED AT &nbsp;KWAKEITHEL ROAD, SAGOLBAND - (FAMOUS FOR PARATHA WITH CHICKEN CURRY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - ELJAY&#39;S, LOCATED AT &nbsp;KWAKEITHEL THOKCHOM LEIKAI - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA AND BURGER)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n8 - NIKHEEL CAFE, LOCATED AT INDO-MYANMAR ROAD, RAGAILONG - (FAMOUS FOR MOMOS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>9 - GREENS THE COFFEE SHOP, LOCATED AT &nbsp;TOP LEIRAK ROAD, KEISHAMTHONG - (FAMOUS FOR COFFEE WITH BURGER AND COOKIES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>10 - SHOSA KITCHEN, LOCATED AT SANGAKPHAM BAAZAAR, CHINGMEIRONG - (FAMOUS FOR BEEF AND PORK DISHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>11 - MICHELLE&#39;S SWEET TEMPTATION BAKERY, LOCATED AT &nbsp;MOIRANGKHOM YAISKUL MAIN ROAD, OPPOSITE TO SAMASAKHI GIRLS SCHOOL - (FAMOUS FOR CAKES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>12 - IMPHAL - {FAMOUS FOR KANGSOI IS A STEW PREPARED WITH DRY FISH, KOBOK, MOLASSES AND RICE ; SINGJU IS A TYPE OF SALAD DISH MADE FROM SEASONAL VEGETABLES ; SANA THONGBA IS A DISH MADE FROM PANEER, GREEN PEAS, CHILLIES, GINGER, ONION, MILK, TURMERIC POWDER, CORIANDER LEAVES AND CUMIN SEEDS}</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(220, 14, 31, 1658, 'Odisha', 'INDIA', 'KONARK', 'sun-temple-299944_640.jpg', 'sun-temple-299944_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Konark, located 65 kms from the capital city of Bhubaneswar, is a beautiful town of stunning monuments and scenic beauty. Set against the bewitching coastline of the Bay of Bengal, this small town holds within itself some of the most marvellous architectural majesties of India. Konark showcases the essence of Odisha&rsquo;s temple architecture. The beauty of Konark is crafted in stone and has been described as a place where the language of stone defeats the language of man. The splendid monuments in Konark are also famous for their religious significance. Konark is renowned world over for the Sun Temple which is also a UNESCO World Heritage Site, the Annual dance festival and its beautiful sandy beaches. Konark also hosts the Sun Festival, where devotees offer prayers to the Sun God by taking dips in the sea. The Dance Festival also hosts a Handicrafts Mela where one can buy unique and exquisitely handcrafted pieces which beautifully reflect the Oriya art form. The third link in the Orissan Golden Triangle, Konark, 35 kms from Puri, is the site of one of the most spectacular examples of religious architecture in the world. Konark derives its name from Konarka, the presiding deity of the Sun Temple. Konarka is actually a combination of two words, Kona means corner and Arka means sun, which, when combined, means the sun of the corner. Konark was one of the earliest centres of Sun worshipping in India. The place finds mention in the Puranas as Mundira or Mundirasvamin, a name that was subsequently replaced by Konaditya or Konarka.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Tourists on a tour to Konark find good number of quality accommodation here. There are adequate decent accommodation options in Konark and the situation is getting better with every passing day. There are a number of star category hotels that rightly cater to every need of a discerning traveller coming to explore Konark or interested in exploring the scenic region around. Konark accommodation comprises of rest house, tourist lodge and guesthouses budget, economy and deluxe class. These accommodations are planned to offer the necessary needs of both the corporate and leisure travellers.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport to Konark is the Bhubaneswar airport. This prominent airport is well linked to all major parts of the country through a number of flights.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail </strong>- The nearest railway stations to Konark are located at Puri and in Bhubaneswar. Both the bustling railway stations are well linked to almost all the major cities and towns in India through regular trains. Konark can be easily reached from these railway stations through taxis and buses that are available.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Konark is well connected by road to major towns and cities in Odisha. An extensive road network connects Konark to the rest of the country via national highways. The State highways link it with prominent cities of the neighbouring states.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Local buses, private vehicles on hire and taxis are the common modes of communication through the road network. Autos, rickshaws and taxis are available in the city. Tourists can also take the local bus service, however it is not up to the standard.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - MAA TARINI SPECIAL BANARAS MITHAPAN, LOCATED IN KONARK - (FAMOUS FOR PAN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - CHANDRABHAGA WOODEN RESTAURANT, OTDC, LOCATED AT PURI-KONARK MARINE DR - (FAMOUS FOR SEA FOOD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - KONARK - {FAMOUS FOR DAHI BHINDI (FRIED EGGPLANT, FRIED FISH, FRIED LADYFINGER DIPPED IN SPICY YOGURT SAUCE) ; ALUDUM IS A DISH MADE FROM POTATOES ; PITHA IS A TYPE OF SNACK MADE FROM RICE FLOUR OR WHEAT FLOUR ; CHHENAPODAPITHA IS A DESERT MADE FROM CHEESE, SUGAR, SEMOLINA, CASHEW, RAISINS, CARDAMOM (ELAICHI) AND DESI GHEE ; MANDIA JAU IS A DESERT MADE FROM RAGI / MILLET FLOUR, JAGGERY OR SUGAR, CARDAMOM POWDER, MILK AND DRY FRUITS}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '');
