(221, 14, 31, 1657, 'Chhattisgarh', 'INDIA', 'KORBA', 'dam-929406_640.jpg', 'dam-929406_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Korba, the power capital of Chhattisgarh is covered with green forests and situated on the confluence of the rivers Ahiran and Hasdeo. It is located at an altitude of 252 meters. There are power plants and is an essential source of electricity in Chhattisgarh. Korba coalfields are also located in the region. The local language of the people here is Chhattisgarhi. The majority of the population comprises of tribal people or Adivasis. Gonda, Kawar, Binjwar, Satnami, Raj Gond etc. are few of the tribes residing in the region. Apart from the major festivals of India many tribal festivals are celebrated in the region namely Pola, Hareli, Karma, Dev Uthni etc. Pola festival is celebrated by the ritual of worshiping bullocks. A bull race is organized during this festival. Hareli is one of the important festivals celebrated by the farmers during the month of Shravan. The farmers worship their agriculture related equipments. The region has a rich social and cultural diversity. The region is popular for the production of the fine silk Kosa which is used in making high quality clothes and is used in dress materials and drapes. Kosa saris are famous worldwide. Kosa saris are sold in haats or local markets over there.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are quite a few two star and three star hotels available in the city of Korba. These hotels are useful for the accommodation purposes of the tourists who visit here. Since there are quite a many tourist destinations in and around the city of Korba, it takes more than a day to travel and explore the city. In such cases, the tourists stay in the hotels for a day or two or even a week to visit the various sightseeing places and explore the city. There are also many budget hotels available as per the convenience of the tourists. These hotels provide all the necessary room and catering services to the guests at affordable rates. Most of these hotels are located nearby station or the airport for the convenience of the tourists.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Raipur is the nearest airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail </strong>- Korba has a railway station on the Chempa Gerva Road. Bilaspur is the nearest main railway station which connects it to the other parts of the country. Many express trains run from Korba.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Buses are available on a regular basis from cities like Raipur and Bilaspur. The National Highway 111 connects Korba to the major cities around it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- The Local transport here includes private buses, state run buses and taxis. Apart from this the local transportation also includes meter taxis and autos. The taxis and autos throughout the city charge a nominal rate depending on the distance covered. There are also shared taxis and autos available for local travel in which the fare in based on per seat basis.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - MADHU SWEETS, LOCATED AT SARDAR VALLABH BHAI PATEL NAGAR, JAMNIPALI - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA CHAAT)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - SUGAR CROWN /CAKE SHOP, LOCATED AT SS PLAZA, POWER HOUSE RD, PURANI BASTI - (FAMOUS FOR PINEAPPLE CAKE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - KOPPER CHIMNI RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT POWER HOUSE ROAD, S.S PLAZA - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN CURRY)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(222, 14, 31, 743, 'Kerala', 'INDIA', 'KOZHIKODE ', 'beach-139888_640.jpg', 'beach-139888_1280.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Formerly known as Calicut, Kozhikode was the Capital of Malabar during the Zamorin rule 500 years ago and is famous for its century&rsquo;s old trade in cotton and spices with Jews, Arabs, Phoenicians and Chinese. Kozhikode is a northern district located on India&rsquo;s South-West coastal belt. The headquarters of this district is also known by the same name i.e. the city of Calicut. Surrounded by the Arabian Sea on the West, this region was the glorious centre of trade and commerce in the bygone era. According to modern day historians, Calicut was best known for its spices and silk- a reason why it had successfully established trade links with many countries in the Indian Ocean. Strong commercial links with many African, Asian and Middle East countries made Calicut a buzzing economic hub in its golden days. Calicut came under the British East India Company during the colonial times and was administered under Madras Presidency. Calicut has its share in the world history for it was in Kappad Vasco da Gama, the Portuguese navigator, landed in the year 1498. This historical moment is honoured by constructing a monument at that place which is a popular tourist attraction in Calicut.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Calicut offers accommodation options to suit every budget. Lodges, home stays and five-star luxury hotels are available in the city and surrounding areas. Backpackers and budget travellers can find rooms in the lodges across the city. Home stays are a good option for stay and the city has a large number of them. Some home stays provide pick up and drop facilities to the airport and internet facility. The city also has luxury hotels and could cost Rs. 8000 and upwards. It&rsquo;s advisable to make reservations in advance.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Calicut International Airport, also known as Karipur International Airport, is situated at a distance of about 25 kms from the city of Calicut. Calicut Airport is connected to almost all major cities of India and some of the cities in the Middle East.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail </strong>- Calicut has a railway station which enjoys remarkable connectivity to all the other cities in Kerala as well as in India. There are frequent trains running to cities such as Chennai, Coimbatore, Bangalore, Delhi, Hyderabad, Thiruvananthapuram, Kochi, Palakkad and Kannur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Calicut enjoys good connectivity by road as NH 17 passes through the district. Calicut city has a major bus station known as the Mofussil Bus Stand which has bus services to a number of towns such as Kannur, Thalassery, Palakkad and Ernakulam. The Kerala State Road Transport Corporation (KSRTC) bus station is located close to the Mofussil Bus Stand from where regular services are available to Bangalore, Mysore and Wayanad. Luxury bus services are also available from Calicut to all major cities such as Bangalore, Mangalore, Chennai and Thiruvananthapuram.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Taxis and Autos are the easiest modes of transport available. Auto Rickshaws, taxis and buses are available from the railway station. Those who arrive by air can hire taxi services from the airport to reach Calicut city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - IN KOZHIKODE - (FAMOUS KOZHIKODE HALWA ; KOZHIKODE BIRYANI &amp; KOZHIKODE BANANA CHIPS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - PARAGON RESTAURANT, ON KOZHIKODE&#39;S KANNAUR ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR PRAWNS AND CHICKEN BIRYANI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - SARABATH MUTHALAI (MILK SHARBAT), NEAR PARAGON RESTAURANT, MANACHIRA - (FAMOUS FOR MILK SHARBAT)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - BOMBAY RESTAURANT, NEAR ST. JOSEPH&#39;S BOY&#39;S HIGH SCHOOL - (FAMOUS FOR BIRYANI &amp; CHICKEN)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n5 - SARVANA BHAVAN, OPPOSITE MOFUSIL BUS STAND, RAJAJI ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR TAMIL BASED VEGETARIAN DISHES)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n6 - AL BAKE ARABIC, AT ALPHONSA BUILDING, MAVOOR ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR ARABIC FOODS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n7 - TOP FORM RESTAURANT, IN MAVOOR ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR CALICUT FISH BIRYANI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n8 - DHE PUTTU, IN EDAPALLY AND ENARKULLAM - [FAMOUS FOR DHE PUTTU (PUTTU IS MADE BY STEEM COOKING LAYERS OF POWDERED RICE ITER SPREAD WITH GRATED COCNUT)]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n9 - GATEWAY HOTEL, IN CITY - [FAMOUS FOR PATHIRI &nbsp;ERACHI (VERY SOFT BREAD COOKED ON BANANA LEAF WITH MEAT STUFED INSIDE AND EARCHI IS CURRY)]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n10 - BOMBAY HOTEL, IN CITY - [FAMOUS ALISA (MADE OF HUSKED WHEAT COOKED WITH CHICKEN)]&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(223, 14, 31, 1652, 'Himachal Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'KULLU - MANALI', 'mountaineerz-1143556_640.jpg', 'mountaineerz-1143556_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kullu, also known as the &#39;Valley of Gods&#39;, is a beautiful district in the state of Himachal Pradesh. The valley earned its nick name because of the belief that it had once been home to many Hindu Gods, Goddesses, and divine souls. Situated at a height of 1230 mts, on the banks of the Beas River, it is known for its magnificent natural surroundings. Originally known as &lsquo;Kul-anti-peetha&rsquo;, meaning &#39;the farthest point of the inhabitable world&#39;, Kullu also finds mention in great Indian epics like the Mahabharata, the Ramayana as well as the Vishnu Purana. Founded by a native of Tripura known as Behangamani Pal, the history of this beautiful hill station dates back to the 1st century. It is said that the region was in accessible until India gained its independence in 1947. This beautiful summer destination is encircled with steep hills, deodar forests, rivers, and apple orchards and is famous among tourists from all across the world for its natural beauty. Apart from this, Kullu is also famous for its ancient forts, religious sites, wildlife sanctuaries, and dams. Considered as an ideal summer destination, the weather of Kullu always remains pleasant during this season. Winters are, however, freezing as the region experiences snowfall during this time. To enjoy outdoor activities and sightseeing, the period between March and June are considered to be perfect while the months of October and November are ideal for river rafting, rock climbing, hiking, and trekking.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are a lot of accommodation options available in Kullu for all pocket sizes. From luxury star hotels to economic accommodation with facilities apt for a comfort stay to guest houses with just basic facilities. Please discuss needs and requirements and negotiate the charges before finally reserving the accommodation. Again owing to its high popularity, tourists coming to Manali are spoilt for choice. There is a wide range of hotels here from budget to luxury resorts for those who wish to splurge. Home stays are also available here.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Bhuntar Airport also known as Kullu Manali Airport or Kullu Airport is the nearest domestic air base located at a distance of around 10 kms to Kullu City.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail</strong> - Joginder Nagar Railway Station is the closest rail link to Kullu, situated at a distance of around 125 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Kullu is well connected with its nearest destinations via state bus services of Himachal Pradesh Transport Corporation. From Delhi, Chandigarh, Pathankot, and Shimla, tourists can avail deluxe buses of the Himachal Pradesh Tourism Development Corporation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Taxis are easily available here for local transport. The nearby attractions can be covered on foot as well.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - JOHNSON&#39;S CAFE, AT CICUIT HOUSE ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR TROUT FISH WITH ROSTED ALMOND &amp; SPANISH PIZZA)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">2 - CASA BELLA VISTA, NEXT TO THICK PINE WOODS IN OLD MANALI - (FAMOUS FOR )</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">3 - FAT PLATE CAFE, AT SHURU, NAGGAR ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR WRAPPED CHICKEN WITH SLUM SAUCE OR TROUT)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">4 - DRIFTER&#39;S CAFE, ON MAIN TEMPLE ROAD, OLD MANALI - (FAMOUS FOR BREAKFAST)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">5 - KHYBER RESTAURANT - (FAMOUS FOR RIVER TROUT)</p>\r\n', ''),
(224, 14, 31, 1655, 'Jammu & Kashmir', 'INDIA', 'LEH', 'beaver-1326585_640.jpg', 'beaver-1326585_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\nThe city of Leh is situated between Karakoram and the Himalayan ranges, on the banks of the Indus River. The scenic beauty of the place attracts tourists from far flung areas all the year round. The greater part of the city is covered with mosques and Buddhist monuments which date back to the 16th and 17th centuries. An ancient, nine storied, palace of King Sengge Namgyal of the Namgyal dynasty, which depicts the architectural style of the medieval era, is one of the major attraction of the place. The population of Leh includes a majority of Buddhist Monks, Hindus, and Lamas. Numerous study centers including, shanti stupas, and Sankar gompas, enhance the charm of the place. Leh city, over the years, has grown as a trade center in Central Asia and offers trading opportunities to several self motivated and dedicated business people. Beautiful lakes and Monasteries, mesmerising landscapes, and mountain peaks are some of the attractive features of this place. The common languages spoken in the state include Ladakhi, Purig, Tibetan, Hindi, and English.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Thongsal Hotel, The Grand Dragon and Hotel City Palace are exotic with charismatic backdrops and scenery. The services here are highly polished and ensure a happy and luxurious stay. Cheaper and budget flexible hotels and inns are also available.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\n<strong>By Air</strong> - Leh is connected to the outside world through air route, all around the year. Kushok Bakula Rimpochhe Airport in Leh is served by Air India, Go Air and Jet Airways. Flights operate daily to Leh, whenever the weather allows. Air India also operates flights from Jammu and Srinagar to Leh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail</strong> - The Jammu railway station is the nearest rail link to Leh, situated at a distance of 734 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- The Jammu &amp; Kashmir State Road Transport Corporation provides regular bus services from Srinagar to Leh, located at a distance of 700 kms. In addition to this, travellers can also avail bus services of the Himachal Road Transport Corporation from Manali to Leh. It takes around 20 hours to reach Leh from Manali on road.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- The mystic and awe striking region of Ladakh is surrounded with gorgeous scenery and travelling through this region can indeed be a pleasure. There are buses, taxis, motorcycles and bicycles available for getting across Ladakh and one can choose the one that deem fit.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">1 - IN LEH LADAKH REGION - [FAMOUS FOR MOMOS ; THUPKA (THICK NOODLE-BASED SOUP WITH VEGETABLES) ; HERBAL TEA (MADE USING FRESH GREEN TEA LEAVES, SALT &amp; BUTTER) ; (SMALL PIECES OF WHEAT FLOUR COOKED IN SUFFICENT QUALITY OF WATER) ; KHAMBIR AND BUTTER TEA (PAN SHAPED LOCAL BREAD) &amp; THENTUK (NOODLE SOUP PREPEARED WITH WHEAT FLOUR DOUGH, MIXED VEGETABLES &amp; PIECES OF MUTTON OR YAK ARE ADDED TO ENHANCE THE TASTE). &nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(225, 14, 31, 757, 'West Bengal', 'INDIA', 'BISHNUPUR', 'tribe-718953_640.jpg', 'tribe-718953_1280.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Bishnupur is called the cultural and religious capital of Manipur. The land where Lord Vishnu resides, the land which is beautifully dotted with dome shaped terracotta temples and the home of the famed dancing deer, Sangai Bishnupur is heavenly. Located 27 kilometres from Imphal, the capital of Manipur, Bishnupur was previously known as Lumlangdong. It is also the district headquarters of Bishnupur district which is bounded by Senapati and West Imphal districts on the north, Churachandpur district on the west, Chandel on the southeast and Thoubal district on the east. The Thangjarok River flows through the town of Bishnupur. Bishnupur is also known as Bishenpur.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Bishnupur has innumerable home stays available. Tourists wouldn&#39;t find anything exotic or very classy here. There are simple budget hotels which would provide with the basic facilities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air </strong>- Imphal Airport is the nearest airport to Bishnupur which is 27 kilometres away from the district headquarters.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail</strong> - Bishnupur, in fact Manipur has no broad gauge rail line. The only railway present in the state is the narrow gauge reaching Jiribam. Thus if, tourists want to travel to Bishnupur through a train, they will first need to reach Dimapur, located 236 kilometres away.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road </strong>- National Highway 150 connects the state capital with Bishnupur and serves as the lifeline to the district. The NH 150 reaching Imphal is connected to the rest of the country through NH 39 reaching Guwahati and NH 53 from Silchar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport</strong> - As this is a small town, one can easily walk around Bishnupur.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1. Bishnupur - (famous for its local sweet Mecha Sandesh, Pera and Posto-r Bora, Chicken chops and Pakodas made from potato, onion, brinjal)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(226, 14, 31, 1652, 'Himachal Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'CHAMBA', 'valley-918504_640.jpg', 'valley-918504_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are many stunning, intriguing places around the world, but very few are as beautiful and awe inspiring as Chamba. Located in the blossom of green mountains with perennial falls and streams, Chamba is one of those places that not only lives up to its image, but exceeds it. A travel to this place evokes many images, fairy tale snow capped mountain vistas, rushing torrent of the Ravi River and beautiful temples. One of the most famous hill stations in India that has been holding a magical allure for travellers, Chamba, a former princely state, is the administrative headquarters of the district of the same name. Chamba the land of lord Shiva is famous for its untouched natural beauty. Chamba, is a small but attractive tourist destination of Himachal Pradesh, is known for its exquisite natural beauty. The place, located amidst picturesque and verdant valleys, is visited by tourist round the year. Sub Himalayan range of mountains, full of diverse flora and fauna, make Chamba an exhilarating experience. Pleasing climate of the place is another factor why Chamba is one among the popular tourist destinations in the whole of India. The summer season in Chamba starts from the middle of April and lasts till the last week of June. Rains in Chamba start in the month of July, when the monsoon breaks-in, and continue till late August or mid September. This is the time when the weather is misty and cloudy. During this time, the entire valley is covered in a hue of light green, with newly washed leaves shining in the glory of after-rain sunshine. In the winter season, the temperature might drop to freezing point in the lower region too and snowfall may happen.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Chamba has hotels in nearly all price ranges, and are easily accessible, and nearly every hotel with a more than 2 star rating has a hospitable staff.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport is Amritsar and Gaggal 136 kms from chamba and is connected by various airlines with Delhi and other cities of India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail</strong> - The nearest railway station is at Pathankot, about 120 kms from Chamba. Buses and Cabs are very easily available from Pathankot to Chamba.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - The HRTC (Himachal Road Transport Corporation) runs regular buses from neighboring states of Delhi, Haryana and Punjab. In the state itself they run to and fro from cities of Pathankot, Shimla, Kangra, Solan and Dharamsala.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Commuting within the city is not a problem since Chamba is majorly a tourist destination. Cabs are readily available; however it is advisable to not travel during monsoons or snowfall since the roads tend to get slippery.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - Desa chicken corner, behined of museum road Chamba - (famous for tandoori dishes and chicken curry with hot Chapattis)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">2 - Olive green restaurant, located on Dogra bazzar chamba - (FAMOUS FOR VARIETY OF DISHES)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - Jagan restaurant, located on Museum street - (famous for Rajma Madara make from different types of spices, yoghurts and butter)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">4 - Chowgan restaurant,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;situated in inside Iravati Hotel - (famous for sweet and sour food dishes made from dried fruits)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">5 - Ravi cafe, located at Jansali - (famous for Indian and Chinese dishes)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n6 - Park view restaurant, located at side of the Bhuri Singh Museum - (famous ror jeera rice and curd dal)<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(227, 14, 31, 1659, 'Manipur', 'INDIA', 'CHANDEL', 'road-220058_640.jpg', 'road-220058_1280.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The Chandel District formerly known as Tengnoupal District came into existence on May 13, 1974. It is the border district of the state. Its neighbours are Myanmar erstwhile Burma on the south, Ukhrul district on the east, Churachandpur district on the south and west, and Thoubal district on the north. It is about 64 kms away from Imphal. The National Highway 39 passes through this district. The district is inhabited by several communities. It is sparsely inhabited by about 20 different tribes. They are scattered all over the district. The district of Chandel has been blessed by Mother Nature, and you will come across different species of flora and fauna in this place. There are many orchids and ornamental plants which are unique to this place. Some of these rare species of plans include the Anisomeles indica, Anotis foetida and the Crasscephalum crepidiodes. Apart from this there are many medicinal herbs which find their way into the local herbal medicine. Candel district is also home to some of the rare animal species with the only ape found in India, the Hoolok Gibbon being found in this district.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Accommodarion is available in Chandel, the most special of which is the forest bungalow.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The Imphal Airport is the nearest air connection to Chandel. Located 8 kilometres from the Imphal city centre and about 65 kilometres from Chandel, the Imphal airport is well connected to the rest of the country via Guwahati.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail</strong> - Manipur doesn&rsquo;t have a railhead. The nearest railway station to Chandel is in Dimapur, Nagaland. Dimapur is located 215 kilometres from Chandel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - The National Highway 39 passes through the Chandel district unto Moreh. Regular bus services and private taxis connect the district to the other parts of the state and country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Cabs are available in Chandel. Private and state run buses also ply in the city.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1. Chandel - (famous for Rajma eromba, Mangal ooti, Chahou Kheer and Paknam)<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(228, 14, 31, 1659, 'Manipur', 'INDIA', 'CHURACHANDPUR', 'sculptures-965116_640.jpg', 'brahma-965116_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Churachandpur is the district headquarters of the largest district in Manipur also called Churachandpur. Locally the town is called Lamka, meaning the &lsquo;place situated at a road junction&rsquo;. The word Lamka is derived from the Manipuri words, &lsquo;Lam&rsquo; meaning path and &lsquo;Ka&rsquo; meaning junction. The district is beautiful as it is surrounded by small hills and narrow valleys. Churachandpur is 59 kilometres away from the state capital, Imphal. It is located in the south western corner of Manipur and covers an area of 4570 km&sup2; and is the largest district within the state of Manipur. The terrain of the district is mainly hilly, with narrow valleys that support wet rice cultivation. Churachandpur town is the district headquarters. However the name Churachandpur is imposed from the name of Manipur Raja Churachand Singh by the Meiteis. It is the second largest town of Manipur, after the state capital, Imphal. Lamka is called the &quot;second town&quot; of Manipur and remains the fastest growing town in the state.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Hotels in Churachandpur are standard business hotels that cater to the needs to the frequent travellers. With basic amenities in all rooms, the hotels here provide guests with a comfortable accommodation that might not be luxurious but definitely is impressive.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - Churachandpur doesn&rsquo;t have any airport, and the nearest airhead is in Imphal, 59 kilometres away. Imphal is well served by all leading airlines in India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail</strong> - Since Manipur doesn&rsquo;t have any significant railway presence apart from the narrow gauge railway station at Jiribam, tourists seeking to board trains to reach Churachandpur will have to travel to Dimapur first.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - The National Highway 150 also known as the Tedim Road connects Churachandpur to Imphal. This road serves as the lifeline to the town and subsequently to the district. Tourists can travel on state run buses or hire private vehicles to reach Churachandpur from Imphal.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport </strong>- The town is also well connected through local means such as auto rickshaws, private taxis and local bus services.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center">1. Life Cafe, JJ Plaza, Rengkai road, Churachandpur, Manipur - (Famous for American &nbsp;and Indian food It is also &nbsp;international coffee shop and sports cafe) &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(229, 14, 31, 1656, 'Nagaland', 'INDIA', 'DIMAPUR', 'raindrops-400101_640.jpg', 'raindrops-400101_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Considered to be among the fastest growing cities of the North East, Dimapur is also the gateway to Nagaland. Once a flourishing capital of a kingdom, today though not the state capital, its infrastructure and facilities are nothing less than that found in capital cities. The word Dimapur is derived from the Dimasa word, &lsquo;Di&rsquo; meaning water, &lsquo;ma&rsquo; signifying big or great and &lsquo;pur&rsquo; meaning city. Thus, Dimapur means the city by the great river. The Dhansiri River flows past the city. Having a rich historical background and being an important city of Northeast, Dimapur has several places of interest. Diezephe Craft Village is located 13 kms from the main city and is supervised by the Nagaland Handloom and Handicrafts Development Corporation Limited. The Rangapahar Reserve Forest is known for housing some rare and endangered birds and animals. It is also one of the main attractions of Dimapur. Once the first headquarters of the Naga Hills District of Assam, Chumukedima is now being promoted as a tourist destination from where the whole of Dimapur along with parts of the Karbi Anglong district can be seen. While visiting Dimapur, a visit to the Triple Falls in a must, as the name suggests, it is a three tier waterfall which is ideal for trekkers and adventurers alike.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Being the biggest commercial city of Nagaland, the city has numerous hotels to stay with low to medium budgets.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - Dimapur is the only city in Nagaland to have an airport and this makes it a very important city. Tourists can easily avail daily flights to Guwahati, Kolkata and Delhi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail</strong> - Being the only city in Nagaland to have a railway station, Dimapur connects the state to the rest of India. There are direct trains from Guwahati, Kolkata, New Delhi and the other metropolitan cities to Dimapur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - There are two National Highways that cross Dimapur. While NH 39 connects Kohima, Imphal and Dimapur to the rest of the country, NH 36 connects Nagaon in Assam with Dimapur. Regular state buses ply on these National Highways and tourists can reach Kohima, the state capital on road.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Commuting within the city is not inconvenient in Dimapur. Tourists can travel in auto rickshaws, cycle rickshaws, buses or taxis here.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1. Breeze Restaurant, Church road, N.S.T. Colony, Dimapur - (famous for delicious food)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n2. Smokey Joe&#39;s Restaurant &amp; Grill, at Middle Colony, Purana Bazar, Dimapur (Famous for snacks) &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(230, 14, 31, 747, 'Meghalaya', 'INDIA', 'JOWAI', 'jowar-223593_640.jpg', 'jowar-223593_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Jowai is one of the growing industrial towns of Meghalaya. It is the district headquarters of the Jaintia Hills district and is largely populated by the Pnar tribe. Jowai is a picturesque town with the Myntdu River surrounding it on three sides and Bangladesh bordering it on the southern fringes. Placed on a plateau, Jowai is situated 1380 meters above sea level. Its high altitude makes the climate pleasant and cool. The Jaintia Hills is mineral rich and there are several coal mines around Jowai. Thus the economy of the place thrives of coal mining. Pristine beauty rests on the hills and valleys of Jaintia Hills. If there are undulating hills in abundance, there is not any dearth of winding rivers all along the way. Jaintia Hills tourism is however not only about natural beauty but its rich history and close connection to present day Bangladesh. The Jaintia king who resided in the capital of the kingdom in Jaintiapur made Nartiang, a small village in these hills as his summer capital. As a result, thorough fare increased, and cultural exchange was strong.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">There are a few accommodation facilities available. More than the hotel, it will be the scenic beauty around which will be the show stealer. Lodging facilities will in all likelihood be adequate and sufficient but nothing extra ordinary.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The airport at Umroi is the nearest airport to the Jaintia Hills. However since it is non-operational currently, the most convenient airport for the tourists planning to take the air route is the Gopinath Bordoloi International Airport at Guwahati.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail</strong> - Meghalaya does not have any railway station in the state and thus the Guwahati railway station is the nearest one. Tourists will get direct transport to Shillong from the railway station.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - National Highway 44 that connects Shillong to parts of Tripura and Assam passes through the Jaintia Hills. It thus serves as a lifeline to all the attractions of the two districts. Tourists will find easy transport from Shillong to all parts of Jaintia Hills.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Local bus services as well as booked taxis are easily available.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(231, 14, 31, 1656, 'Nagaland', 'INDIA', 'KIPHIRE', 'palm-1274006_640.jpg', 'palm-1274006_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kiphire is one of the small towns of Nagaland that is located in an exotic location overlooking the Saramati Mountain, the highest mountain peak of Nagaland. Kiphire is also the name of a newly formed district that was carved out of the Tuensang district in 2004. It is the ninth district of Nagaland. The Tuensang district bounds the Kiphire district in the north, Phek district is on the west while the Kiphire district shares an international border with Myanmar in the east. Kiphire is 239 kms from Kohima, the capital of Nagaland. Kiphire is home to a few Naga tribes, namely, Yimchungers, Khiamniungan, Phom, Sangtams and Sumis. According to folklore, the Yimchungers originated from the nearby place called Kemephu near the Waphur village.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Hotels, Homestays, Dorms, Shacks and Resorts are easily available.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - Since Nagaland is served by only the Dimapur airport, to reach Kiphire tourists have to take a flight to Dimapur first and then travel on road. Dimapur is 471 kms from Kiphire and takes about 8 hours on road.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail</strong> - Dimapur also has the only railway station in Nagaland. Thus if want to travel to Nagaland on train, one will first have to reach Dimapur then take the road to reach Kiphire.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Kiphire is well connected to the rest of Nagaland by the National Highway 155. The national highway connects Kiphire to Kohima, Meluri, Dimapur, and Mokochung. Regular state transport buses and private taxis are available from anywhere in Nagaland to Kiphire. The state highway also connects Tuensang, Kiphire and Meluri together.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center">1- KIPHIRE - (Famous for Dried Pork, Anishi, Pongsen, Crab Chili Sauce, Naga Ghost Chili Sauce)&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(232, 14, 31, 1656, 'Nagaland', 'INDIA', 'LONGLENG', 'orchid-172206_640.jpg', 'orchid-172206_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Longleng is the district headquarters of the newly created district of Nagaland Longleng. Along with Kiphire, it is one of the newest districts of Nagaland. Longleng was declared a full fledged district on 24th January, 2004 and was carved out of the Tuensang district. It is situated at an altitude of 1066 mts above sea level. Tourists need to issue an Inner Line Permit to enter Longleng. The Phom Nagas inhibit Longleng. The Phom Nagas are exceptionally good with pottery, spinning and bamboo work. Traditionally, the Phom Nagas have also been into agriculture. The origins of the Phoms cannot be quite ascertained, but from oral tradition it can be deduced that this tribal group too emerged from stones, similar to the Ao Nagas. The Phom Nagas have mostly converted into Christianity and thus have modernized to a large extent. However, during festivals they can still be found wearing vihe ashak or nempong ashak, which are shawls wrapped around the body. The Monyu Festival that is celebrated to herald the summers is celebrated with much pomp and fanfare.</p>\r\n', '<p>Really affordable hotels and guest houses are available.</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - Dimapur Airport is the only airport in Nagaland and thus if want to reach Longleng by air, one have to first, board a flight to Dimapur and then take the road further on.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail</strong> - Longleng doesn&rsquo;t have a railway station, and the nearest railway station is at Dimapur located 642 kilometres away.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road </strong>- National Highway 61 connects Longleng to Changtongya and is severed by buses and private tourist vehicles. The nearest town to Longleng is Mokokchung while Kohima is 230 kilometres away.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1- LONGLENG - (Famous for its Roasted Intestines, Bitter Melon, Chicken Glutinous Rice Soup and boiled vegetable)&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(233, 14, 31, 1656, 'Nagaland', 'INDIA', 'MON', 'dawn-1845018_640.jpg', 'samui-1658583_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Home of the Konyaks nagas, Mon provides tourists with a unique and quite mesmerizing view of tattooed faces wearing feathery loin cloths. The District, with the exception of the foothills, has a difficult terrain with steep slopes. Even though Mon doesn&#39;t have a lot of sightseeing points, but it still attracts a lot of people from all around the world. The people, their culture, their dressing is very colourful and different and it is probably the most interesting aspect of this town. There are numerous villages nearby which are very pretty and might offer you a closer picture of the life of the Nagas. Veda Peak and Naganimora are among the famous tourist spots here. One can see a waterfall near the Veda peak and this would be one of the most pristine places in the region. Veda peak is located around 70 kilometres from Mon. Among the few villages in the region that are worth visiting are Chui, Longwa and Shangynu. An adventure trip for many, an experience of a lifetime for several others and an anthropological hotspot for enthusiasts, Mon has something stored for everyone.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Mon has a couple of government tourist bungalows which provide a decent stay when operational. There are a few other hotels as well, with basic facilities. Most hotels aren&#39;t very lavish. Expect a simple, comfortable stay here.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest airport to Mon is Guwahati 479 kms, Jorhat 157 kms and Dimapur 296 kms. From all these places travellers will get easy conveyance in the form of state transport buses or tourist taxis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail</strong> - Lakwa railway station route to Sivasagar, Assam is one of the nearest railways stations to Mon. Lakwa is located 75 kilometres away from Mon.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - &nbsp;Dimapur is the nearest transit point and one can reach the place using taxis easily.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport </strong>- A small beautiful town and commuting within is easy. Tourists can walk or take cars on rent to explore the area.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1- MON - [Famous for Chicken Breast(made from Chicken ,Onion Powder,Green Beans, Carrots in Mushroom Gravy)]&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(234, 14, 31, 751, 'Punjab', 'INDIA', 'LUDHIANA', 'sikh-658516_640.jpg', 'sikh-658516_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Ludhiana is a district in the Indian state of Punjab. It is located on the south banks of River Sutlej. It is quite aptly called as the &quot;Manchester of India&quot; for its world famous hosiery products. Apart from being an industrial town, Ludhiana is home to several places of tourist interest that draws in a large number of tourists from various parts of India. Tourism in Ludhiana is flourishing and gaining popularity and it is now an important stopover in the itinerary of the tourist who is on his tour of Punjab. It is an important pilgrim centre of Punjab and one will come across lots of temples, sacred shrines and Gurudwaras located all over the city. The most fascinating landmark of the town is the 500 years old Lodhi Fort built by Sikander Lodhi located near the Sutlej River. The Maharaja Ranjit Singh Museum is another place to visit during travel to Ludhiana. Earlier known as Lodi-Ana-Lodi&#39;s Place, Ludhiana was home to the Lodi Dynasty. Now, it is one of the manufacturing hubs of India.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Many low budgets to luxury hotels can be found around the railway station. If looking for comfort or luxury, hotels in Ludhiana have everything to delight you. This famous commercial town of Punjab welcomes tourists with a number of luxury properties. No matter whether have a tight budgets or wish to spend without worries, Ludhiana, the proud city of Punjab will meet with the expectations.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air </strong>- The Sahnewal Airport also known as Ludhiana Airport is situated on GT Road, around 12.3 kms away from the main city. With regular flight services provided by Air India and other renowned airlines, tourists can conveniently reach Ludhiana from New Delhi and other major cities in the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail </strong>- There are numerous trains like Frontier Mail, Jammu Tawi and Shatabdi Express operating on the New Delhi-Amritsar route that halt at Ludhiana. Ludhiana is connected by daily and weekly trains to several Indian cities, including Jammu, Jalandhar, Amritsar, Patiala, Delhi, Mumbai and Kolkata.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Ludhiana is connected to numerous cities of Punjab and nearby states by public and private buses. Located on the Amritsar Delhi Grand Trunk Road, Ludhiana can easily be reached by buses from major cities like Amritsar, New Delhi and Chandigarh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Autos are the best way to cover Ludhiana. Private cabs and hire car services are also available here.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - BABA&#39;S CHICKEN, IN LUDHIANA - (FAMOUS FOR BUTTER CHICKEN &amp; TANDDORI CHICKEN)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - ZIMIDARA DHABA, IN LUDHIANA - (FAMOUS FOR DAL MAKAHNI &amp; PANNER MATAR)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - BANSI VAISHNO DHABA, IN LUDHIANA - (FAMOUS FOR SARSON AK SAAG AND MAAKE KI ROTI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - BASANT, IN LUDHIANA - (FAMOUS FOR PUNJABI KADHI)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(235, 14, 31, 1652, 'Himachal Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'MANDI', 'mountains-263895_640.jpg', 'tiger-8057_6405.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Mandi, also known as &#39;Varanasi of Hills&#39;, is a well known district situated in the state of Himachal Pradesh. Situated on the banks of the River Beas, the historic city of Mandi was earlier known as Mandav Nagar after the great Sage Mandav. Packed with thick green cover of pine trees, deodar trees and tea plantation, this geographical area is also ingrained with rich culture and heritage in form of its numerous temples spread all across the town. Mandi, a popular commercial hub of Himachal Pradesh is simply much more than that. Lying on the banks of River Beas, Mandi also displays some old palaces and exquisite form of colonial architecture. With a blend of warm and cold weather, the city housing the lakes and gardens provide for its travellers a breath of fresh air. Serving as a gateway to some famous valleys such as Kullu, Manali, Spiti and Lahaul, Mandi is must on north India itinerary which never fails to enchant its visitors. The geographical area of Mandi is covered with green forest cover, which includes pine and deodar forests and tea plantations. The climate of Mandi remains warm and pleasant in the months of April, May and June. The best time to visit Mandi is in between the months of March and October.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Mandi being a commercial centre of the state, it offers variety of accommodation options. From highly economical hotels and guest houses to premium and deluxe resorts, Mandi is packed with such options with great food and service.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air -</strong> The Bhuntar Airport is the nearest air base to Mandi, located at a distance of about 59 kms from the town. The airport is connected to major Indian cities like Shimla, Delhi, and Mumbai with regular flights.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail </strong>- The Kiratpur Railway Station is the nearest rail head located at a distance of about 125 kms from Mandi. This station is well connected with all major cities of India via Chandigarh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road </strong>- Travellers interested in exploring Mandi District can visit the destination by bus. State owned buses, which connect Mandi to its neighbouring cities, can be availed by tourists to reach the destination.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport </strong>- The main source of transportation within the city is auto-rickshaws, private vehicles and buses. Travellers can also hire taxis or cab to commute from one place to another but it is far more convenient to find autos which are available 24X7.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - IN MANDI - [(FAMOUS FOR CHANNA MADRA ; ALOO PALDA ; MASALA FRIED OKRA &amp; AURIYA &nbsp;KADOO (MADE BY PUMPKIN WITH MUSTARD SEEDS)]<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(236, 14, 31, 742, 'Karnatka', 'INDIA', 'MANGLORE', 'sea-1416631_640.jpg', 'sea-1416631_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The port city of Mangalore is well known for its tall swaying coconut palms, temples and pristine beaches. Despite the growing commercialization, it provides a quick and soothing getaway from the city hustle bustle and yet preserves just the right amount of the urban glitter. It provides a pleasant natural environment and makes it close to perfect with its shopping attractions with grand complexes and a vibrant sea food culture. Major tourist attractions in Mangalore are the beautiful beaches and the temples, churches and mosques. Mangaladevi temples, KREC beach, Someshwara beach, Panambur beach, Tannirbavi Beach, Seemanthini Bai Bajai Museum are some of the places one might want to visit. Yakshangana the folk dance of Mangalore is the perfect visual treat to add colour to trip and casts a spell as one witness the magnificent culture that it sustains and glorifies. Mangalore is a beautiful city in Karnataka state of India that greets visitors with its line up of coconut trees. The trees stand tall in most parts of Dakshina Kannada and in the neighbouring state Kerala as well. Once called South Kanara district is currently called Dakshina Kannada. Mangalore is a major port in the district and for the whole Karnataka state.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are multiple hotel options for tourists, extending from high end resorts to budget hotels and even beach resorts. The list of hotels and restaurants in Mangalore is unlimited. For the business class and tourists there are many places to stay and enjoy. The hospitality is good enough to please the visitors. Hotels are not only in the city but there is a beach resort at Ullal. For the foreigners visiting Mangalore it is a very nice place to stay.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The Mangalore Bajpe airport is well connected to all major cities and towns of India. The Mangalore airport is located at a distance 10 kms from the heart of the city. Regular flights that connect it to major cities are available from this airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail</strong> - Mangalore Central and Mangalore Junction are the two stations of Mangalore. This city is connected to Bangalore, Chennai, Mumbai, Hassan and various other important cities through its broad gauge and metre gauge railway tracks.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Mangalore can be approached through NH-13, NH-17 and NH-48 by road. Karnataka State Road Transport Corporation (KSRTC) buses are available from Mangalore to various other destinations within the state. Dakshina Kannada Bus Operators Association (DKBOA) buses are also available.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - White coloured taxis and auto rickshaws are available for local transport. Private bus and cab services are also available.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - GIR MANJA&#39;S&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;NEAR KALIKAMBA TEMPLE, GOPAL KRISHNA TEMPLE ROAD, BUNDER, BHAVATHI - (FAMOUS FOR VARIETY OF DISHES)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">2 - GAJALEE NEAR CIRCUIT HOUSE COMPOUND, KADRI HILLS - (FAMOUS FOR COSTAL FOOD)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">3 - WOODLANDS, AT BUNTS HOSTEL ROAD, BALMATTA - (FAMOUS FOR DOSA)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">4 - SHETTY LUNCH HOME, IN DON BOSCO HILL CROSS ROAD, HAMPAN KATTA - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN GHEE ROAST)<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '');
