(237, 14, 31, 751, 'Punjab', 'INDIA', 'MOHALI', 'man-290186_640.jpg', 'man-290186_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Situated in the Indian state of Punjab, Mohali, now named as Ajitgarh, is a satellite city of Chandigarh. It is one of the three cities that collectively form the Chandigarh Tricity Chandigarh and Panchkula in Haryana being the other two. Mohali is officially known as SAS Nagar in the memory of Sahibzada Ajit Singh, the eldest son of Guru Gobind Singh Ji. Conceived after the trifurcation of Punjab, Mohali was a part of the Rupnagar District until the government of Punjab declared it as a separate district in 2006. Over the time, this city in the suburbs of Chandigarh has undergone massive development and is today targeted by several outsourcing IT companies including international firms like Quark, Dell and Philips. There is a lot to see for travellers opting for Mohali tourism, starting from the magnificence of Mohali Cricket Stadium to the mesmerising beauty of Sukhna Lake. Rock Garden, Chhatbir Zoo, Sukhna Wildlife Sanctuary, Rose Garden and Bhakra Nangal Dam are among other popular places of tourist interest near Mohali.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Being located in Punjab, hotels in Mohali offer one to savour a taste of Punjab hospitality. The surrounding areas enveloped with crystal clear lakes, clean streets and green paddy fields make visitors explore the city repeatedly. There are good number of accommodation options ranging from best 3 star properties to mid budget hotels and cheap hotels. The city lacks in luxury properties but it will not disappoint if looking for good hotels, laced with all the modern amenities. There are number of budget hotels in Mohali.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport to Mohali is in Chadigarh. This is a domestic airport and is 10 kms far from Mohali. Raja Sansi International Airport is the nearest International airport which is in Amritsar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Mohali is Just 10 kms from Chandigarh and at Chandigarh railway station one will get a good number of trains that are connected to many other cities in India. Kalka Shatabdi, Sampark Kranti, Dehradun Express are some of them.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Mohali is well connected to all over India by bus service. It is a very inexpensive and comfortable way to reach Mohali City Guide. Tourists can use either government buses which are low in fare, and there are private AC and luxury buses also.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - KATANI SWEETS AND DHABA, LOCATED AT KUMBRA VILLAGE, SECTOR 68, SAHIBZADA AJIT SINGH NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR POORI CHANA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - GOBIND DAIRY &amp; SWEETS, LOCATED AT SCF 17, PHASE 11, SECTOR 65, SAHIBZADA AJIT SINGH NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR RASMALAI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - BANSAL NAMKEEN, LOCATED AT S.C.F-65 PHASE-7, S.A.S NAGAR MOHALI - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA AND SANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - POLKA THE CAKE SHOP, LOCATED AT SCF-68 , MOHALI, PHASE 3B-2, SECTOR 60 - (FAMOUS FOR CAKES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - NOOR DAIRY PHASE 5, LOCATED AT 321, MOHALI BYPASS, PHASE 5, SECTOR 59, SAHIBZADA AJIT SINGH NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR RASGULLA AND GULABJAMUN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - KHURANA BROTHERS SWEETS PRODUCTS, LOCATED AT BAY SHOP 139, PHASE 7, SECTOR 61, SAHIBZADA AJIT SINGH NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA AND PAKODA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - FOOD MOOD, LOCATED AT SHOP NO .298 OPPOSITE PHASE 4 TELEPHONE EXCHANGE, PHASE 5, SECTOR 59, SAHIBZADA AJIT SINGH NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR EGG ROLL)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>8 - PAPPA JI DHABA, LOCATED AT SCF - 49, PHASE -7, SAHIBZADA AJIT SINGH NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR ROASTED CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>9 - ML MANSAROVAR DHABA, LOCATED AT PLOT NO. 3, KAMLA MARKET, PHASE 1, SAHIBZADA AJIT SINGH NAGAR, SAHIBZADA AJIT SINGH NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR CURRY-CHICKEN AND CURRY-MUTTON)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>10 - NEW CHARLIE&#39;S FOOD, LOCATED AT 28, SCO, MOHALI STADIUM RD, SECTOR 71, SAHIBZADA AJIT SINGH NAGAR - (&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;FAMOUS FOR AALOO PARATHA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>11 - SHAMA DHABA, LOCATED AT 698, MATTAUR, SECTOR 70, SAHIBZADA AJIT SINGH NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN BIRYANI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n12 - THE GAPPA BAR, LOCATED AT BOOTH NO- 25, MOHALI STADIUM RD, PHASE 7, SECTOR 61, SAHIBZADA AJIT SINGH NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR GOL GOPPA(PANI PURI))</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(238, 14, 31, 1656, 'Nagaland', 'INDIA', 'MOKOKCHUNG', 'village-1192158_640.jpg', 'village-1192158_1280.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">A visit to the pristine state of Nagaland is not complete without a visit to Mokokchung, an important district headquarters of the state. Primarily populated by the Ao tribe, Mokokchung is also the third largest urban centre of Nagaland after Dimapur and Kohima. Mokokchung is also considered to be the cultural and intellectual capital of the state. The town is located at an altitude of 1325 mts above sea level. This Ao land is gifted by Nature with gurgling streams and picturesque hills. Northern Assam is close to Mokokchung. Mokokchung comes alive during Christmas, New Year and the Ao festival called Moatsu. It has become traditional now to herald the New Year every year with fun filled activities that run past midnight with people happily participating in the festivity leading to the main town square. Mokokchung is the most significant urban centre in all of Nagaland after Dimapur and Kohima and the home of Ao Naga.&quot;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>There isn&#39;t a whole variety of hotels. The few lodges are quite decent and very reasonable.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest airports to Mokokchung are in Dimapur located at a distance of 212 kms and Jorhat located at a distance of 105 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail </strong>- The nearest railway station to Mokokchung is Mariani in Assam. The strategic location of Mariani ensures that all the major trains running towards Dibrugarh.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Mokokchung is well connected by road through the National Highway 61 that runs from Kohima to Amguri via Wokha, Mokokchung, Changtongya and Tuli. The Nagaland State Transport runs regular buses from Mokokchung to Kohima, which lies at a distance of 162 kilometres.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Not a huge place, so commuting within the town is easy. One can walk or take cars on rent to roam around the area.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(239, 14, 31, 747, 'Meghalaya', 'INDIA', 'NORTH GARO HILLS', 'ancient-waterfall-1363655_640.jpg', 'ancient-waterfall-1363655_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">North Garo Hills District is blessed with natural and scenic beauty. A vast majority of the District is still covered in green. An untold many tourist places are waiting to be discovered by the outside world. The district of North Garo Hills forms the Northern most part of Garo Hills. It is the gateway to the entire Garo Hills region and shares a border with Assam. The population is a mixture of indigenous Garo tribes along with other minor tribes comprising of Rabhas, Hajongs, Kacharis, Boros. The climate is sub tropical with adequate rainfall. The people are an ethnic mix of Indo Burmese Tibetan ancestry. Forming the western part of the State the entire Garo Hills having an area of approximately 8,000 sq kms is densely forested and hence one of the richest spots in bio&not;diversity.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are quite a few lodges and &#39;hotels&#39; here. Keep expectations low and then one will have a wonderful time. It might be very tough to find for an accommodation in an on season.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The only airport in Meghalaya is in Umroi, 25 kilometres from the capital of the state, Shillong.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail </strong>- The Guwahati railway station serves as the main railhead to all of Meghalaya. Tourists can easily find a train from any part of the country to Guwahati.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road </strong>- National Highway 51 and National Highway 62 crosses the North Garo Hills district and is the main lifeline to all the towns and villages of the district. Apart from the National Highways, there are several state highways that connect these places together.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport </strong>- To get around the place, the best modes of transport are the auto rickshaws and the taxis. The auto rickshaws do not ply on meters and hence the prices are negotiable, meanwhile the taxis are costlier than the auto rickshaws.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><em>1 - NORTH GARO HILLS - {FAMOUS FOR GAL&rsquo;DA NA&rsquo;KAM IS A DISH MADE WITH DRY FISH AND GREEN VEGETABLE ; DO&rsquo;0 MODIPOL IS A DISH MADE FROM CHICKEN, GINGER, RAW PAPAYA, CHILLIES AND BAKING SODA ; WAK JO.KRAPA IS A DISH MADE FROM PORK, TOMATO, CHILLIES, ONION, GARLIC, CUMIN, AND TURMERIC POWDER ; NA&rsquo;KAM BITCHI IS A Soup MADE FROM DRY FISH, GREEN CHILLIES, GINGER, BAKING SODA AND WATER}</em><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(240, 14, 31, 1660, 'Arunachal Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'ANJAW', 'mountains-1645078_640.jpg', 'mountains-1645078_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Anjaw is a small offbeat town amidst enormous greenery, gleaming waterfalls, beautiful river streams, pine forests and a thousand other spectacular things. Anjaw is not a much developed tourist destination, but due to its natural surroundings and greenery, it is a place where one can find solitude away from the noise of the cities. Anjaw in Arunanchal Pradesh is a newly born district after its split from the Lohit district in 2004. River Lohit, a tributary of Brahmaputra flows by this city which situated 1296 mts above sea level and is the eastern most district of India; just 20 kms away from the India China border. People who visit this place not only appreciate the beauty of the nature, weather and ethnicity but also indulge in adventure sports activities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Hotels or guest houses in Anjaw provide basic amenities at nominal charges.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Flight </strong>- Closest airport is in Tezu. There are also helicopter services available from Tezu to Hayuliang. Guwahati, Lokpriya Gopinath Bordoloi International Airport is the nearest major airport with regular flights connecting to the major cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Road </strong>- Anjaw can be reached by NH52 and there are bus facilities available at nominal costs. These buses are available from other closer cities like Tezu, Daparjito, Pasighat, Along and Ziro.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Train </strong>- Closest railway station from Anjaw is the Tinsukia railway station in Assam.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Getting Around</strong> - The intra city commuting is not that developed but there are buses available to travel within the cities and the tickets of these buses are cheap. These buses may not be the most luxurious way of travelling though.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(241, 14, 31, 1660, '', 'INDIA', 'CHANGLANG', 'mountain-landscape-640617_640.jpg', 'landscape-640617_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Changlang District shares international boundary with Myanmar and is best known for its bio diversity and scenic beauty and a unique culture that makes it standout from the nearby areas. Changlang has a subtle uniqueness in its attitude, nature and environment, hinting towards an exotic and distinct identity. What it shares, however with the rest of the state is lush green surroundings, pleasant environment and picturesque sceneries. One can visit the Namdampa National Park and enjoy the nature&rsquo;s blessings to the area. As per folklore, the name &lsquo;Changlang&rsquo; was derived from a hilltop called &lsquo;Changlangkan&rsquo;, where the natives discovered an herb that can be used for poisoning fish in the river. Changlang District is bounded by Lohit District and Tinsukia District of Assam in the north, by Tirap District in the west and by Myanmar in its southeast. Patkai Bum Hills, which are the extensions of the Greater Himalayas reaching up to Nagaland, is the natural barrier between Changlang and Myanmar. Changlang town is the administrative headquarters of Changlang District.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Budget hotels are easily available with basic facilities and comfortable sleep.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The closest airport is located at Dibrugarh and this has connectivity to places such as Delhi, Kolkata, Itanagar, Guwahati and Dimapur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail </strong>- The closest railway station is located at a place called Tinsukia. The place is connected to cities such as Chandigarh, Dibrugarh and Amritsar and this is the most suitable option.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Changlang town can be reached from Dibrugarh, Tinsukia, Margherita and Miao by road.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport -</strong> Taxis and jeeps are the best option to travel to the place. Travelling by cars is also an option.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>CHANGLANG - (FAMOUS FOR NGATOK IS A TYPE OF CURRY MADE FROM FISH AND VARIOUS SPICES)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(242, 14, 31, 1660, 'Arunachal Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'DIBANG VALLEY', 'mountain-1663700_640.jpg', 'mountain-1663700_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">A very beautiful place situated in between Twang and Bomdila, Dibang Valley is located in the state of Arunachal Pradesh and was created out of Lohit district in the year 1980. It is located on the banks of the River Dibang which flows through this valley. Dibang Valley Travel guide is incomplete without a mention of its innate beauty and rich heritage. The district is very rich in its wildlife. Uncommon mammals such as Red goral, Mishmi takin and Gongshan muntjac are found in Dibang Valley and Sclater&#39;s Monal is the rare species of birds which can be seen in the district. The capital of the district, Anini is located in the northern part of northeast India. Being situated at the Indo China border, the district has a strong Chinese impact. The picturesque valley offers a beautiful view for the tourists. The snow peaked mountains, deep gorges, turbulent rivers cascading down the hills, numerous waterfalls, placid lakes, archaeological sites, peace and fun loving hospitable people and above all the heavenly climate make Roing one of the most attractive destinations for tourists. A natural heaven with mountains and lakes, it is one of the most exciting places in Arunachal Pradesh. This town won&#39;t let anybody down. Anini is where the clouds come down the kiss the land. With much of its beauty peeking from behind the misty air, this unexplored town is the place to visit for pristine calmness. Lying in the beautiful Dibang Valley district, Anini is marked by pleasant weather and immense natural beauty, making it a tourist&#39;s paradise, appearing from the clouds. Its silence, beauty and magic is almost untouched and can relax tourists to the very core.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">The Anini Circuit house is one of the most comfortable places to stay in Dibang Valley. Simple lodges and hotels are available in plenty too. Various hotels and guest houses are also available in Roing.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Flight</strong> - Dibrugarh is the closest airport and buses to Dibang Valley from there are available frequently. Dibrugarh is well connected to cities like New Delhi, Kolakata, Guwahati, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Road </strong>- The best way to reach Dibang Valley is by road. Connection is decent and the drive is beautiful.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Train </strong>- Tinsukia is the closest railway station and is very well connected to cities like New Delhi, Chennai, etc. Many Rajdhanis stop here too. Rail connectivity is comfortable and cheap.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Water</strong> - Ferries in addition are also available to Dibang Valley, which can be boarded from Dolaghat.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Local Transport </strong>-&nbsp;If have your own vehicle, then things will be very convenient. Getting cabs will be easy too. Travelling via car is the best option.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(243, 14, 31, 1660, '', 'INDIA', 'EAST KAMENG (SEPPA)', 'hut-1681485_640.jpg', 'hut-1681485_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Located in the state of Arunachal Pradesh and an ultimate place to visit, East Kameng is one of the largest districts of Arunachal Pradesh in India. Seppa is the district headquarters of the city and major area of the region remains covered with the Himalayas. East Kameng Travel guide is incomplete without a mention of its rich cultural and spiritual legacy. Most of the tribal people carry out a form of slash and burn agriculture which is known as Jhum. Presently, horticulture based on apples and oranges is becoming progressively more popular in the town. The region around the Kameng River has conventionally under the lead of the Mon kingdom, Bhutan, Tibet and the Ahom kingdom. Lamaism got a powerful foothold among the tribal groups as early as in the 7th century, where the Kachen Lama founded the Lhagyala Gompa in Morshing.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>There are a lot for deluxe and medium to budget accommodation options nearby East Kameng.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest International Airport from Seppa is Lokpriya Gopinath Bordoloi International Airport, Guwahati, roughly 358 kms from the town.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail</strong> - The nearest railway station is located at Tezpur named as Tezpur Railway Station, roughly 200 kms from Seppa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Seppa is well connected by roads to the other cities of the state and to Assam. The roads are not very well maintained and hence it is advised to have a sturdy vehicle like a Gypsy, jeep, Innova, Sumo etc. The inner line check post is located at Bhalukpong, which is the entry and exit point for Arunachal Pradesh and hence it has good road connectivity with other cities of Arunachal. There are two routes from Itanagar the state capital to reach Seppa. One is through Bhalukpong around 430 kms and one through Sagali around 210 kms.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SWEET BHALUKPONG (SWEETS SHOP), LOCATED AT &nbsp;NH229, CONA, BHALUKPONG - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA AND BESAN CHAKKI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - EAST SIANG - {FAMOUS FOR APANG(RICE BEER)}</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(244, 14, 31, 1660, '', 'INDIA', 'EAST SIANG (PASIGHAT)', 'lake-1031102_640.jpg', 'lake-1031102_1280.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Home to river Brahmaputra which transcends down from Tibet, this place is a photographer delight for comprising abundant sceneries of nature and is the oldest town in the state. Pasighat is known as the &#39;Gateway of Arunachal Pradesh&#39; and is a pure heaven for nature lovers. If looking for adrenaline rush, then this is also a great place as adventure activities like white river rafting, boating and angling similar to fishing will certainly set one rolling here. A unique blend of peace and adventure is what makes this place a must visit. Pasighat was founded in 1911 AD by the British as a gateway to administrative convenience of the greater Abor Hills and the north area in general. Primarily there were settlements of Pasi and Minyong communities who are still living in the villages in and around Pasighat. However, this place still has the beauty and the culture intact and it hasn&#39;t lost its charm as commercial tourism is yet to reach here. Located at an altitude of 153 mts above sea level, Pasighat rests on the banks of the river Siang. Agriculture is the major occupation of the locals here. Apart from rice which is the major food crop cultivated here, there are also many tea gardens close to the place. Tourism is also a major source of income of Pasighat along with agriculture and horticulture.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Various budget hotels and guest houses are available.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air</strong> - The Lilabari Airport is the nearest airport to Pasigarh. There is also an airport in Mohanbari in Dibrugarh which is not too far from the place.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Rail</strong> - The nearest railway station to Pasighat is in Murkong Selek in Assam.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Road </strong>- Pasighat can be reached by road from the nearby cities in Arunachal Pradesh and Assam. It is just an overnight journey from Guwahati.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Travelling by cars is the only option.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(245, 14, 31, 1660, '', 'INDIA', 'KRA DAADI (JAMIN)', 'hill-1209988_640.jpg', 'hill-1209988_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Kra Daadi District is an administrative district in the state of Arunachal Pradesh in northeast India. It is a newly created district, having been split from Kurung Kumey district on 8th February 2015. &nbsp;The district borders Tibet to the north. Jamin, located 20 kms from Palin is the district headquarters. Kra Daadi has two assembly constituencies, namely Tali and Palin, covering the seven circle headquarters of Chambang, Gangte, Palin, Pipsorang, Tali, Yangte, and Tarak Langdi. Kra Daadi is one of 20 districts located in north eastern Indian state Arunachal Pradesh. There are total 2 blocks which comes under Kra Daadi district, and there are total 158 villages which come under this district. Summers are warm with very high rainfall; winters are mild with moderate rainfall. It is very hilly with high geographical terrain and most of the time it is covered by clouds. The area is windy in nature.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Kra Daadi is situated in the western side of Arunachal Pradesh. From the capital city Itanagar it is the district highway connects Kra Daadi to rest of the state. Regular Bus and Tata Sumo services are available from Itanagar, Ziro.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Public transport facility is available.</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(246, 14, 31, 1660, '', 'INDIA', 'KURUNG KUMEY (KOLORIANG)', 'glacier-national-park-1733311_640.jpg', 'glacier-national-park-1733311_1280.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Koloriang is a beautiful hilly district headquarter town of Kurung Kumey district in Arunachal Pradesh bordering China. It is surrounded by high mountains all around and is located in the right bank of river Kurung, one of the major tributaries of Subansiri River. The climate is rainy and hot during summer and very cold in winter. The Bengia, Chera, Nangram, Chello, Riya, Yumlam clans of Nyishi community inhabits the area. People are known for their honesty, straight forwardness and their attachment to their age old customs and traditions. Longte is the annual festival of the area where people enjoy with festivity and pray different Gods and Goddesses for protection and well being of humanity, livestock and general prosperity. It is celebrated in the month of April every year. It can be reached by road from Itanagar, the capital of Arunachal Pradesh and Guwahati and other towns of Assam. Visiting them can be an exciting experience and the local population is hospitable. The villages of Sangra, Palin, Deed and Talo are located nearby.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>There is an inspection bungalow that is located here and this is the only place that offers accommodation.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport to Koloriang is Lilabari Airport in Assam which is about 245 kms away. The nearest International Airport is the Lokpriya Gopinath Bordoloi International Airport in Guwahati, which is about 600 kms away.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail </strong>- The nearest railway station to Koloriang is Harmoti Station in Assam which is about 250 kms away.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road </strong>- Koloriang is well connected to the neighbouring towns by well maintained roads. Tourists can hire a taxi/cab to reach Koloriang. Jeep and Gypsy is the ideal mode to reach Koloriang. Visitors generally prefer Koloriang as a stop by town during their tour to other cities of Arunachal.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(247, 14, 31, 1660, '', 'INDIA', 'LOHIT (TEZU)', 'fence-470221_640.jpg', 'fence-470221_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Tezu is a small town situated in the Lohit district of Arunachal Pradesh. This small town is known for its beautiful valley and rivers. The ancient inhabitant of this land of valley and rivers are the Mishmi tribes. These tribes were in existence since the time of Mahabarata. It was said that Lord Krishna&#39;s first queen Rukmini was a Mishmi Damsel. The people of Tezu celebrate Mishmi festival known as Tamladu puja, a major festival for the Mishmi tribes. The festival is celebrated on the 15th of February each year and people from all the communities are invited to join the celebrations. The small town of Tezu also has some important tourist attractions. Some of the important tourists for travellers are Parshuram Kund, a famous pilgrimage place which attracts thousands of Hindu pilgrims from all over India and also from the neighbouring countries. Travellers come here to take a holy dip and wash away the sins. This is followed with a fair at Tezu and takes place every year during the month of January. Situated just 25 kms away from the famous Parasuram Kund Lake, it is a perfect hill station to chill out with family and friends. It is located at an elevation of 185 mts above the sea level. Famous for its scenic beauty, adventure enthusiasts can enjoy trekking, hiking and river rafting in Tezu also. There are also facilities for trekking from Tezu to glow lake which takes one day, hiking and river rafting and angling on the river Lohit. The hill station is home to indigenous tribes like Mishmi, Khamti, Digaru and Miju. Among the famous is, Mishmi Tribes, which have traditions and customs dating back to the Mahabharata times.</p>\r\n', '<p>Hotels or guest houses in Lohit provide basic amenities at nominal charges.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air </strong>- The town of Tezu has a small airport; however this is generally used for charter flights. The closest commercial airport is located at Mohabari. It is located in the city of Dibrugarh and there are frequent flights services from places such as Kolkata, Guwahati, Itanagar and Delhi to the airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Rail </strong>- The closest railhead is located at the town of Tinsukia and arriving by rail is the most comfortable option. The station is well connected to other cities of India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Road </strong>- Daily bus services are available from Tinisukia 140 kms via Namsai and by ferry from Dholaghat to Sadia and by bus for Sacha for Tezu and Bhismaknagar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Tezu can be easily accessed by road, taxis and buses are the main modes of transport to the place.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(248, 14, 31, 1660, '', 'INDIA', 'LOWER SUBANSIRI (ZIRO)', 'goat-1596880_640.jpg', 'goat-1596880_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">One of the oldest towns of Arunachal Pradesh Ziro is a small beautiful hill station surrounded by rice fields and is nestled between a clusters of beautiful pine trees. The large forest areas spread over the entire region is a home to tribal people. This small beautiful town is situated at an altitude of 1500 mts from the sea level. The rich flora and fauna and its biodiversity make it an ideal destination for nature lovers. The Apa Tani tribe here worships nature God and earn their livelihood by making handicrafts and handloom products besides wet land cultivation. The Apa Tani tribal people are not nomadic like the other tribes. They are permanent inhabitants of the region Ziro. The major tourist attractions of Ziro are the green serene Talley Valley, the hillock Ziro Putu, Tarin fish farm, the tall idol of Shiva linga at Kardo. Several festivals are celebrated by the Apatani people namely the Myoko festival in March, the Murung festival in January and the Dree festival in July. The climate of Ziro varies from season to season. Tourists visit Ziro throughout the year. The climate is dependent on the terrain and the location of the place. The months of October and November are the period of transition. However throughout the year relative humidity is high except in winter.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Various budget resorts can be found here. Nothing fancy but decent stay with basic amenities like hot water, etc. will be provided.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest Airport is Lilabari Airport in Itanagar. Flights are available from all cities like Delhi, Kolkata and Guwahati.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail</strong> - Railway Station Itanagar to Ziro is just 147 kms. Ziro does not have its own railway station and the nearest railhead is at Tezpur 144 kms. The town of Tezpur is well connected from various parts of the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Road State government buses are available from the town of Itanagar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport</strong> - It is possible to hire a rickshaw for nearby tourist spots. Hiring a taxi or Tata Sumo is the most preferred and by far the safest option.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1- LOWER SUBANSIRI(ZIRO) &nbsp;- (FAMOUS FOR THUKPA IS A NOODLE SOUP IT CONTAINS CHILI POWDER AND GARAM MASALA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(249, 14, 31, 739, 'Haryana', 'INDIA', 'PANIPAT', 'mongolia-1567608_640.jpg', 'horse-1567608_1280.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Panipat is a well known tourist destination in Haryana. Three historic battles were fought here which changed the course of the history of India. The city and district, also by the same name, are home to countless monuments of great historic and cultural interests. Panipat also finds mention in the first verse of Bhagwad Gita where it is referred to as dharamkshetra. Its historical roots apart, Panipat, is also known as the &lsquo;city of weaver&rsquo; and is famous for its handloom products which are in great demand in India and are also exported abroad. Panipat has several monuments, buildings and museums to its credit. The Panipat Museum houses contemporary art and craft and also showcases the history of the region through interesting displays. You can also visit the old fort, an ancient fort, which is mostly in ruins. Like other cities and towns in India, Panipat too has its share of religious sites. The Kabuli Shah Mosque is an ancient structure, which was built by Emperor Barbar, the founder of the Mughal dynasty in India. Innumerable monuments, forts, temples and its magnificent historical connections make Panipat in Haryana an interesting tourist destination. Panipat was one of the five cities founded by Pandava brothers during the times of Mahabharata.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Panipat has a good collection of star rated and budget hotels; there are excellent 4 star hotels in Panipat with lavish facilities catering to all the essential and luxury demands. A wonderful yet affordable stay can be enjoyed at budget accommodations in Panipat which offer their guests a wonderful vacation without digging much into their pockets.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport is the Delhi Airport. Panipat is about 130 kms from Delhi. From Delhi, one can hire a taxi or take the public/private transport bus to Panipat.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail</strong> - Panipat is well connected to major cities in India by train. Panipat railway station receives trains from cities such as Jammu Tawi, Delhi, Mumbai and Jaipur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Panipat is situated on GT Karnal Road and is about one hour drive from Delhi by pass. The town is well connected by public and private transport buses from Delhi, Ambala, Karnal and other major cities and towns in Haryana and neighbouring states.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Lots of public transport options are available in Panipat. One can move around in buses, autos, rickshaws and cabs as well.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - MITTHAN SWEETS, LOCATED AT PATEL NAGAR, TEHSIL CAMP - (FAMOUS FOR JALEBI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - BOSA RAM SWEETS, LOCATED AT BOSA RAM CHOWK, MODEL TOWN ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSAS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - AGGARWAL SWEETS, LOCATED AT CHULKANA ROAD, SAMALKHA - (FAMOUS FOR BHAJJI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - FOOD GARAGE, LOCATED AT MODEL TOWN - (FAMOUS FOR CHILLI POTATO)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - BUNNY, LOCATED AT SHOP-10,DADA POTA MARKET,NEAR SALARJUNG GATE,SUKHDEV NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - LUXMI RASOI, LOCATED AT HUDA SECTOR 11, HUDA - (FAMOUS FOR LASSI AND FRUITS CREAM)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - LUXMI SHUDH BHOJNALYA, LOCATED AT GEETA COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR DAL FRY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>8 - AMRITSARI SAMOSE WALA, LOCATED AT SUBHASH BAZAAR, AMAR BHAWAN CHOWK AREA - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>9 - ANNA, LOCATED AT RAM LAL CHOWK, MODEL TOWN - (FAMOUS FOR DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>10 - CHANANA SWEETS, LOCATED AT NEAR LAL TANKI MARKET, RAM LAL CHOWK, MODEL TOWN - (FAMOUS FOR MANCHURIAN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>11 - JOLI EXPRESS, LOCATED AT SHOP NO 1 , LAL TANKI MARKET, RAM LAL CHOWK, MODEL TOWN - (FAMOUS FOR BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>12 - PAHWA SWEETS, LOCATED AT BARSAT ROAD, ANSALS SUSHANT CITY, HUDA - (FAMOUS FOR CHOLE SAMOSAS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>13 - AHUJA SWEETS, LOCATED AT ANSALS SUSHANT CITY, HUDA - (FAMOUS FOR MASALA DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>14 - PEARL DHABA, LOCATED AT SEWAH - (FAMOUS FOR SANDWICHES, COLD COFFEE AND AALOO PARATHA)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(250, 14, 31, 1660, '', 'INDIA', 'PAPUM PARE (YUPIA)', 'chile-1104794_640.jpg', 'chile-1104794_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Yupia is located about 22 kms from the capital of the state, Itanagar. Yupia in Arunachal Pradesh is the headquarters of Parum Pare district. The Yupia Capital Complex sub division consists of the terrain of Yupia, along with the entire Parum Pare district, is primarily mountainous. There are three types of forests in Yupia tropical mixed evergreen forest, tropical evergreen forest and the mixed forest. So Banana, Bamboo and Cane form the majority of the natural vegetation of Yupia. Animals like wild boar, barking deer, elephants, flying squirrels and samber populate these forests. The canopy like forest also houses a wide range of birds, including woodpeckers, kingfisher, parakeets, mynas, trogon, hornbill, swifts, barbets and cuckoo. As far as the population of Yupia is concerned, it is comprised of Nishis and the Mikirs. Yupia is a popular place for indulging in adventurous activities like hiking and trekking, as the necessary amenities are available here in plenty. Tourists can also take a trip to the Jawaharlal Nehru State Museum in the region, which is a popular tourist destination in Yupia. The Buddhist Gompa in Yupia is also very famous among travelling pilgrims and tourists.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Options for accommodation in Yupia might not be too many; hence it would probably be better to stay at Itanagar, which is only 20 kms away from the town<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Flight</strong> - Closest airport is Lilabari airport in Assam at a distance of approximately 87 kms. While for international flights, the option is Lokpriya Gopinath Bordolio International Airport in Guwahati which is about 339 kms away from Yupia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Road</strong> - Yupia can be easily reached by hiring taxis or boarding a bus from anywhere in Arunachal Pradesh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Train </strong>- Closest railway is Harmuti railway station located at a distance of about 59 kms from Yupia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Yupia is close to Itanagar, the state capital of Arunachal pradesh and Yupia is well benefited by the developments taking place in Itanagar. So, even the transportation services are pretty smooth in this region. There are bus services, taxis and rickshaws available for commuting with ease.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - JYOTI RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT &nbsp;BANK-TINALI ROAD, C- SECTOR - (FAMOUS FOR PARATHAS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - CHEENU SWEETS, LOCATED AT NATIONAL HIGHWAY 52A, CONA, ITANAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR RASHUGULLA AND GULAB JAMUN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - PAPUM PARE - {FAMOUS FOR WUNGWUT NGAM &nbsp;(CHICKEN WITH RICE POWDER) ; PASA, IT IS FISH SOUP PREPARED FROM FRESH RAW FISH}</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(251, 14, 31, 751, 'Punjab', 'INDIA', 'PATHANKOT', 'sunset-1097625_640.jpg', 'sunset-1097625_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Pathankot is located in the district of Gurdaspur of Punjab of Northern India. Pathankot is the meeting point of three states, Punjab, Himachal Pradesh and Jammu &amp; Kashmir, which makes it an important gateway to many North Indian holiday destinations. Situated in the picturesque foothills of Kangra, with the river Chakki flowing close by, Pathankot city is a stopover to tourists heading to Amritsar, Shimla, Dalhousie, Dharamsala, Kangra Valley and Jwalaji. Pathankot is at a distance of 476 kms from Delhi, 112 kms from Amritsar and 246 kms from Chandigarh. The strategic location of Pathankot has earned it the name of &#39;Cock Neck City&rsquo; since it connects Jammu&amp; Kashmir with the rest of India. Pathankot has lush green vegetation which is supported by Ravi and Chakki rivers on its two sides. Pathankot has a rich historical past as it was under the reign of many rulers. It was the seat of the Loi and shawl weaving industry for many centuries. It was also a prime spot in the trade route maps leading to Central Asia. Several names were attributed to Pathankot during different centuries. In the late 17th century, Pathankot was a part of the Nurpur Kingdom, former name for Himachal Pradesh, founded by Jatpal, a Taur Rajput who came from Delhi. However the name Pathankot is derived from the migration and settlement of Pathans during the medieval period, according to historians. The name Pathankot stands for &lsquo;Fort of Pathans&rsquo;. Today, Pathankot has emerged to become a major commercial hub of Punjab. Due to its strategic location, Pathankot serves as a base for the defence forces Indian Army and Indian Air Force. Pathankot is also home to Mamoon Cantonment, the largest military station in Asia.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Many good hotels are easily available. Luxury hotels, 3 star hotels, 2 star hotels and even cheap accommodation are available in the city. One can make the selection based on factors like popularity, price and names etc.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">By Air - The Pathankot airport is mostly used by the Indian Air Force as an airfield. However, there are few flights that operate from and to Delhi and Kullu for civilians. The Amritsar airport is the nearest international airport to Pathankot, around 108 kms away.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail </strong>- Pathankot has two railway stations Pathankot and Chakki Bank, which are managed by the Northern Railways. Being a gateway to many popular tourist destinations in North India, this place is well connected to major parts of the state and country. The luxury train Kangra Queen also passes through Pathankot.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - The bus stand in Pathankot is named after Maharana Pratap, a famous Rajput chief. Himachal Transport Corporation, Punjab State Transport Corporation, Haryana Roadways and Jammu State Transport offer frequent bus services to Pathankot. Apart from this, many private buses are also available for tourists.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Tourists can take an auto rickshaw or a bicycle rickshaw at cheap rates.</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(252, 14, 31, 1653, 'Uttarakhand', 'INDIA', 'BAGESHWAR', 'four-thousand-islands-141801_640.jpg', 'four-thousand-islands-141801_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Bageshwar is a temple town of Uttarakhand which is situated amidst mountains. There are many temples in this city which are mostly dedicated to Lord Shiva. The convergence of river Saryu, Bhagirathi and Gomti makes this place more beautiful. Picturesque mountains, natural backdrops and people living in the foothills of mountains, all this makes Bageshwar city tranquil and magnificent. This town is considered to have the blessings of Lord Shiva and hence possesses a spiritual significance. Lots of temples, fairs and beautiful markets are the prime attractions of this place. As this place is situated in the foothills of mountains hence one can also enjoy the fun of trekking, mountaineering, camping and sightseeing. There are so many glaciers around the city which can be explored for their natural waters and snow white ice. The spiritual plane of this place attracts lots of tourist from around the country to visit this city who also enjoy the natural environment and serenity of this place. There are so many other places where one can go in excursions to add more fun to the visit. Bagnath Temple, Hanuman Temple and Thingal Bhairav Temple are some of the famous temples in this city which are must visit places in Bageshwar.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The issue with hotels in Bageshwar, since quite a while remains that the pricing of the rooms is as per 4 star hotels, but the hotels themselves are no more that 2 to 3 stars. It&#39;s imperative to exercise caution while choosing accommodation here and have booking stone before hand, with proper research, than to shuffle around the city with luggage in the middle of the trip.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air </strong>- Nearest airport to this place is located in Dehradun i.e. Jolly grant airport which is directly connected with selected cities of India via domestic flights.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail </strong>- The nearest railhead to this place is located in Kathgodam town which has direct trains from Delhi, Lucknow and other major cities. It is the last stop of trains that come to Uttarakhand. This place is located nearly 180 kms from Bageshwar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road </strong>- The nearest connecting towns to Bageshwar, are Ranikhet and Almora, about 98 kms away. It takes approximately about two hours to reach Bagheshwar from these places.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Cab and taxi services are possibly the only thing available with ease in the city of Bageshwar. Map out the journey and quote the same while physically booking the cab to avaoid hidden pricing, or even overpricing for that matter. Bargain till can&#39;t do more, and make this offbeat retreat, an economical one too. Within the town, a lot of walking can also be done to explore the region.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - ANIL RESTAURANT, LOCATED IN BAGESHWAR - (FAMOUS FOR CHOWMIEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - MANGAL&#39;S, LOCATED AT BARI KHALSA - (FAMOUS FOR JALEBI)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(253, 14, 31, 1652, 'Himachal Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'BILASPUR', 'ramparts-285280_640.jpg', 'ramparts-285280_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Bilaspur is a hill town near Shimla, famous for its forts and Gobind Sagar Lake, a man made reservoir considered the lifeline of the district. Bilaspur, India&#39;s first planned hill station, is popularly known for its artificially made lake which is called the Gobind Sagar Lake on Sutlej River. It is a beautiful lake where one can rejuvenate and participate in water sports and fishing. Also, this lake provides water to the very famous Bhakra Nagal Dam. Bhakra Dam is the highest dam in India and it is also the highest straight gravity dam in the entire world. This dam located on the foothills of Himalaya offers spectacular views of the Gobind Sagar Lake. Apart from this, the road bridge on the Gobind Sagar Lake at Kandraur is highest of its kind in Asia.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Bilaspur is slowly picking up on tourism and one can find quite a few hotels to stay in the main town area.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> -The nearest Airport from Bilaspur is Shimla Airport, roughly one and half hours drive from Bilaspur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail</strong> - The nearest Railway Station is Kiratpur Sahib Railway Station which is located at a distance of 65 kms from Bilaspur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Bilaspur is very well connected to Chandigarh and Ambala through road by National Highway No 22. Shimla and Solan in Himachal are also connected to Bilaspur by this road.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Either drive down in own car or travel by the local buses. One can hire a car from the car rental company in Chandigarh.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', '');
