(254, 14, 31, 1653, 'Uttarakhand', 'INDIA', 'CHAMPAWAT', 'rice-194768_640.jpg', 'rice-194768_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Champawat is a magnificent hill station situated amongst the Himalayan ranges. It is a district located in the Kumaon region of Uttarakhand. The place is well known for splendidly designed temples which date back to 10th century. It is supposed to be the capital of Chand rulers. The Nagnath and Bhaleshwar temples are some of the fine examples of the temples with great architectural design that existed during 10th century. According to the Hindu mythology, it is believed that the Kurma incarnation of Lord Vishnu in the form of Tortoise appeared in the Champawat. That is why the district of Champawat holds great importance among the devotees of lord Vishnu. The hill station is known for its impressive natural beauty in the form of snow clad mountains, lush green forest, clean river and beautiful landscape. Its pleasing climate also makes it an ideal tourist destination. These terrains can lead the trekkers to various destinations, such as Vanasur, Purnagiri, Kanteshwar Manch, Tanakpur, Pancheshwar, Vyasthura and Lohaghat. Champawat is also associated with the movement started by Swami Vivekananda. The Prabbudh Bharat publication started by Swami Vivekanand was started in Champawat. A gripping journey of self exploration and challenging terrain, Champawat is not a usual retreat. Visitors will be pushed to physical and mental limits, because this place gives a lot to explore, without having to deal with any over intrusive and money gobbling guides around. One will find the usual elaborately carved temples and riverside tourist spots here, but Champawat leaves more than enough room to explore it.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Being a very pleasant tourist destination the place has numerous hotels with proper facilities to cater the travellers&rsquo; demands. There is no such best season to visit Champawat. That is why the rooms are always booked throughout the year. There are about 5to 6 hotels available that offer a reasonable rate per night, and have been reviewed as being some of the best in the area.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The Naini Saini Airport of Pithoragarh is the closest air base, located around 80 kms away from Champawat. The Pantnagar Airport is also an alternative for tourists to reach the destination. Tourists can avail taxis from both these airports to reach Champawat.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail </strong>- Tanakpur railway station is the nearest railway station to Champawat and is situated at a distance of 75 kilometres from the city. The train services connect it with various other cities in Uttarakhand.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Buses are available to Champawat from various nearby destinations, including Nainital. Both AC luxurious and non AC buses are available to Champawat. Tourists can also take buses from Pithoragarh to the destination, which is located at a distance of 74 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Commuting within the city is mainly via taxis, and tons of car varieties are available to suit the budget. Tourists can also travel by buses within the city but the buses are a more time consuming option, however, a superior option if looking at cutting costs.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(255, 14, 31, 1652, 'Himachal Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'HAMIRPUR', 'trees-1210028_640.jpg', 'trees-1210028_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">A very beautiful and alluring tourist destination to plan your holidays, Hamirpur is located in the state of Himachal Pradesh and lies in a relatively colder area in western Himachal Pradesh. It is the district headquarters of Hamirpur district and is surrounded by Mandi to the east, Una to the west, Kangra to the north and Bilaspur to the south. Hamirpur is a perfect place for nature lovers and a must visit place for those fond of scenic beauty. Hamirpur Travel Guide is full of references to the serene spots and religious places. Vyasa Cave, Kotkahlur Fort, Bachhretu Fort, Naina Devi Temple and Gobind Sagar Lake are the famous tourist attraction nearby Hamirpur.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Don&rsquo;t expect luxury or deluxe accommodation options in Hamirpur. The places to stay at the major towns in the valley include the sub-divisional headquarters where one can find State Tourism Department&rsquo;s Tourist Bungalows besides several private hotels.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest Airport from Hamirpur is Shimla Airport, roughly three hour drive from Hamirpur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail </strong>- The nearest Railway Station is Kiratpur Sahib Railway Station which is located at a distance of 120 kms from Hamirpur.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road </strong>- Taxi/Bus services are available from Una to Hamirpur. The city of Hamirpur is well connected with the rest of the country by road. Hamirpur is at a distance of about 480 kms from Delhi.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - A9 FOOD COURT, LOCATED AT HIRANAGAR CHOWK,OPPOSITE HHH - (FAMOUS FOR WHITE SAUCE PASTA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - PIZZARO, LOCATED AT NATIONAL HIGHWAY 3, PRATAP NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - HOT SPOT, LOCATED AT SHIV MANDIR, NEAR 177001, KUDHAR - BHUDHWIN ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA AND NOODLES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - CHOPSTICKS THE FAST FOOD CORNER, LOCATED AT KOHTA, CHAKMOH, KOHTA - (FAMOUS FOR MOMOS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - FLAVOURS RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT KRISHNA NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN GRILLED SANDWICH)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n6 - SAI SWEETS, LOCATED AT SHIMLA-KANGRA RD, KOHTA - (FAMOUS FOR BARFI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - PANDITAN DI HATTI, LOCATED AT NEAR DEGREE COLLEGE, ANU - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA AND BESAN KA PAKODA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>8 - JAGDAMBE SWEETS, VERMA &amp; SONS, LOCATED AT VILLAGE BASSI, POST OFFICE BHORANJ - (FAMOUS FOR JALEBI,AND SOMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n', '6,8,23,29'),
(256, 14, 31, 1652, 'Himachal Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'KASAULI', 'solan-110131_640.jpg', 'solan-110131_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kasauli is a popular hill station located in the district of Solan in the state of Himachal Pradesh. Situated at an elevation of around 1800 mts above sea level, this place finds mention in one of the great Indian epics, the Ramayana. According to the mythology, the Hindu monkey god, Hanuman, stepped over this place while returning with the Sanjeevani Hill. The destination received its name from a mountain stream flowing between Jabli and Kasauli known as Kausalya. During the 19th century, Kasauli became an important part of the Gurkha territory. Later, the place was converted into a major battalion town by the British. It is in this place that several Indians including locals joined the Britsh army. In 1857, when the first battle for Indian Independence or the Sepoy Mutiny took place, Kasauli also saw an insurgency among the soldiers from India. These men joined hands with the Gurkhas but later were left behind after the Gurkha rebellions backed out. These soldiers were brutally punished by the British officials.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">a). Solan<br />\r\nSolan, a beautiful district located in the state of Himachal Pradesh is also known as the &lsquo;Mushroom city of India because of the extensive mushroom farming in the region. Nestled at an elevation of 1467 mts above sea level, Solan is known for its scenic beauty. The place received its name from the Hindu Goddess Sholoni Devi, who is also the main deity of the region. The entire region is enveloped with dense forests and high mountains. The Matiul Peak, standing at a height of 1986 mts, is situated in the east of the city and can be easily seen from here. To the north of the city is the Karol Peak, which is the highest peak of the region. Solan serves as a base for trips to other famous hill stations like Kandaghat, Kasauli, Chail, and Dagshai.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">b). Arki<br />\r\nArki is a major tourist destination located in the district of Solan, Himachal Pradesh. The smallest town of the district, it provides the travellers an opportunity to visit some of the most exotic tourist destinations of the region. Historically, this town was the former capital of the ancient hill state of Baghal, which was founded by Raja Ajai Dev during 1660-65 AD. Situated at a distance of 52 kms from Shimla, Arki still has some monuments that represent the royal heritage of the former rulers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">c). Nalagarh<br />\r\nFar away from the chaos of cities, Nalagarh is known for its abundant greenery, serenity and the amazing view of the Shivalik hills past the Sirsa River. The Mughals and the Britishers during their rule cherished the beauty of this place and regarded it as a princely state and till date the royal touch is still alive and unscathed. Besides the regal attributes attached to the place, Nalagarh successfully embraces the growth in steel, chemicals, thread mills, leather and breweries and is an upcoming industrial town. The place is surrounded by the view of the outer Himalayas on one side and the Shivaliks on the other. The place is sprinkled with the ruins of many forts around the valley, which include the forts of Chamba, Surajupur, Ramharh and Malaon.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">d). Kandaghat<br />\r\nKandaghat is a small town and Tehsil in the Solan district of Himachal Pradesh. The road to the famous tourist destination of Chail turns from Kandaghat. The beautiful view of the valley and the chilling weather is the main attraction of the place. One should definitely visit Kandaghta if looking for is a quiet and serene vacation. In recent times, it is one of the most popular tourist destinations in India. This place offers fantastic tourist attractions as well as amazing cuisine that tourists can enjoy in the blissful weather.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are plenty of accommodation options available in Kasauli. From small cottages to guest houses to luxurios resorts, Kasauli has something to offer to everyone. Being in close proximity to Kasauli, Solan has a variety of options of accommodations to choose from. For tourists who are looking to splurge on a luxurious stays there a few heritage hotels in this region that match international standards on luxury and comfort. The Arki Fort which has now been converted into a heritage hotel is one place where tourists looking for luxury and comfort can stay. Arki also has a few budget hotels. One might not find a large number of options in hotels in Nalagarh though the closest cities Baddi and Chandigarh has good accommodation facilities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Chandigarh Airport situated 59 kms from Kasauli is the nearest air base to the destination. This airport is well connected with other Indian cities like New Delhi, Kolkata, Mumbai, and Srinagar. Travellers can hire taxis from outside the airport to reach Kasauli.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail</strong> - The closest railhead to Kasauli is the Kalka Railway Station, which is located at a distance of around 40 kms. The railway station at Kalka is well connected with major places in the country like New Delhi, Kolkata, Amritsar, and Mumbai.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Regular state owned buses ply from different cities of Himachal Pradesh for Kasauli. Travellers can avail deluxe and super deluxe buses from Chandigarh and Delhi for Kasauli.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Taxis are easily available to go around the town. One can easily avail HRTC buses in Solan. There are no established modes of local transport available in Arki so it&#39;s best to take a cab. One might find some rickshaws. Travelling in Nalagarh is quite easy with options like buses and taxis. Most of the hotels also provide taxi services at nominal charges.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - NARINDER SWEETS, LOCATED AT MALL ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR JALEBI, GULAB JAMUN AND SAMOSA)&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - NH22 DHABA, LOCATED AT NATIONAL HIGHWAY 22 - (FAMOUS FOR BUTTER CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - CAFE RUDRA, LOCATED AT SHOP NO. 24, HERITAGE MARKET, SOLAN DISTRICT - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN SANDWICHES, CHICKEN IN HOT GARLIC SAUCE AND CHEESE OMELETTES)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - CAFE MANTRA, LOCATED AT SHOP NO. 8, HERITAGE MARKET - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN BIRYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - KASAULI CAFE, LOCATED AT MALL ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR MOMOS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - SHIBI SWEETS AND NAMKEEN, LOCATED IN KASAULI - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA AND KHASTA KACHORI)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(257, 14, 31, 1653, 'Uttarakhand', 'INDIA', 'KASHIPUR', 'road-1245901_640.jpg', 'road-1245901_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Famous as a gateway towards beautiful hills of Nanitam, Kashipur is a home to many gods and goddesses. Located in the district of Udham Singh Nagar in dev bhoomi Uttaranchal the city was also known as Govisham and currently it is known as Kashipur named after Kashinath Adhikari. It is an amazing tourist spot for travelers who are planning to visit Nanital. Main Kashipur attractions are Drona Sagar Lake, Shree Bheema Shankar Mahadev, Maa Bal Sundari Mandir, Shri Bhole Baba Pathari Wale Temple, Gurdwara Sri Nankana Sahib and many others that draw attention from large number of travelers every year. The minion town of Kashipur is emerging as a major industrial centre. Many big industrial houses such as India Glycols Ltd, HCL, Videocon, GAMA IFRAPROP Private Ltd. have already set their foot in Kashipur. The city also has its own 225MW Power Plant, paper mills and sugar mills. Some of the main industrial estates located in Kashipur are the Balaji Industrial Estate, Bheem Nagar Industrial Estate, Omega Industrial Estate and IDEB Industrial Estate. Kashipur is the only city of Uttarakhand which features its only IIM that is IIM Kashipur, a public business school located in Kashipur. It is one of the thirteen Indian Institutes of Management which the government has set up during the Eleventh Five year Plan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">a). Rudrapur<br />\r\nThe city of Rudrapur is located in Indian state of Uttarakhand and is known to be the seventh most populated city of the state. The city has recently experienced a rapid growth in various sectors, including education and employment. Rudrapur can be seen as an apt example of &#39;Unity in Diversity&#39;, with a number of cultures and religions found here. Although the city is experiencing rapid development in various fields, about 70 percent of the population of Rudrapur is dependent on agriculture. The city has a number of ancient monuments located here, which are main Rudrapur attractions and are definitely worth visiting. A famous religious spot of the city is Atariya Temple, where a large number of visitors come each year. Chaiti Devi Temple is another famous religious spot of the city, and is also seen as a major tourist attraction. This temple is considered as a sacred place within the city and people come here to offer their prayers. Striking features of the place which attract people here are its peaceful ambiance and beautiful location. The city is surrounded by green hills which add to the scenic views. The city has efficient connectivity of various modes of transportation.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\nThere is a wide variety of hotels ranging from budget low cost economical hotels to luxury deluxe hotels, from home stays to heritage hotels and resorts in Kashipur and Rudrapur.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Pantnagar airport is the nearest airport which is located around 68 kms from Kashipur. Pant Nagar Airport is well connected by metalled road with Kashipur. It is a domestic airport and its nearest International airport is New Delhi.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail </strong>- Kashipur is well connected by railway networks with major destinations of India. Udham Singh Nagar Railway Station is situated 2 kms from Kashipur city.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Kashipur is well connected by motor able roads with major destinations of northern India. Taxis are easily available from major destinations of Uttarakhand to Kashipur.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - BHAJ GOVINDAM, LOCATED AT RAMNAGAR ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR DAL MAKHANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - ANNA BAKERS &amp; FOOD PLAZA, LOCATED AT RAMNAGAR ROAD, OPP JINDAL KOTHI, UDHAM SINGH NAGAR DISTRICT - (FAMOUS FOR PATTIES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - OM SWEETS, LOCATED AT NH 121 - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - FRESH N&#39; FILLIN, LOCATED IN KASHIPUR - (FAMOUS FOR SANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - BHAJ GOVINDAM, LOCATED AT RAMNAGAR ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR CHILLY PANEER, MUSHROOM CURRY, DAL MAKHANI, AND NAWABI HALWA)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(258, 14, 31, 1652, 'Himachal Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'KINNAUR', 'road-1130859_640.jpg', 'road-1130859_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Kinnaur, also known as &quot;Land of god&quot; is about 235 kms from Shimla and is known for its serenity and beauty of the lush green and rocky mountain scape having Satluj, Baspa and Spiti River snaking through it. A brotherly fusion of Hinduism and Buddhism at one place reflects the existence of a culture of a different sort which is well preserved by its people in this era of modernization. Hindus visit Kinnaur to see the famous Kinner Kailash, believed to be the home of Lord Shiva and the Shivaling rocks, the stories of Pandavas and their link with Kinnaur is a great attraction. There are also old Buddhist monasteries and temples in the vicinity which hold special importance and are revered by Buddhists. Apart from religion, Kinnaur also has a large scope in adventure sports like trekking and skiing. There are about nine known routes for trekking and some which are five day or six day trips. Kinnaur is well known for its delicious apples, Chilgoza, handlooms and handicrafts materials. Slight traces of modernization can be seen in the town, its cultures and people but the area continues to be pristine, simple and magnificently beautiful.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Kinnaur offers a sufficient choice of hotels, most of which would be found in the capital, Reckong peo. There are different ranges of hotels which cater to the need of every category of customers. Budgeted or luxurious hotels do maintain facilities like gym, cyber cafe, air condition, spa and many others. Picturesque location with astounding features that and serene beauty leaves visitors spell bound with mesmerizing moments etched in their memory for life.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air </strong>- Shimla Airport is nearest to Kinnaur, which is located at a distance of 249 kms from Kalpa, which is the chief village of Kinnaur District.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Rail </strong>- Nearest railhead to Kinnaur is the Shimla railway station, which is situated at a distance of around 230 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Road </strong>- Travellers can avail buses for Kinnaur from the nearby places such as Shimla and Rampur. Bus and taxi services can be availed at affordable prices.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Some of the routes in Kinnaur are really rough and challenging however, buses and taxis are readily available here but there are some regions which could not be covered by them and people walk by foot to reach such destinations.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(259, 14, 31, 1652, 'Himachal Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'LAHAUL AND SPITI', 'hills-1207998_640.jpg', 'hills-1207998_1280.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Lahaul and Spiti are perfect locations for nature lovers and trekkers too. Located at an altitude of 3340 mts in the north eastern corner, these are the two remote villages of Himachal Pradesh. Before these two districts were combined, the Lahaul capital was Kardang and Dhankar was the capital of Spiti. But now, these are spread over an area of 13835 sq kms and as per 2001 census, the total populations of these districts were recorded around 33,224. The breathtaking snow capped hills and the craggy beauty of these regions lure the travellers. Lahaul and Spiti are two isolated Himalayan valleys of Himachal Pradesh that lie on the Indo Tibet border. A beautiful land of captivating Buddhist art and culture Lahaul is distinguished by inflicting mountains and glaciers while the vegetation, climate and the landscape of Spiti are similar to that of Tibet. That&#39;s why the village of Spiti is also popular as &#39;Little Tibet&#39;. Holidays in Lahaul and Spiti offer pleasant experience whilst unfolding the stunning valleys of these places. In the year 1960, Lahaul Spiti became the districts of Himachal Pradesh that have a perfect combination of Hinduism and Buddhism. Both have their own speciality like Lahaul is blessed by nature and fostered by Chandra and Bhaga Rivers while on the other side Spiti is a living museum and there are breathtaking trek routes, valleys and very popular monasteries that captivate tourists who visit here from different parts of the world. Spiti is famous as the &#39;Land of the Lamas&#39;, and the Tabo Monastery situated here has been acknowledged as a UNESCO World Heritage Site, and includes scriptures and wall paintings like Tankhas and Stucco.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are just a few rest houses, some hotels, tourism guest houses in Kaza which is the headquarters of Spiti subdivision of the district. There are also a lot of accommodation options in Keylong, which is the headquarters of the Lahaul subdivision of the district.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Lahaul &amp; Spiti is well connected to road. Private and government buses are available on here.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Jogindernagar is the nearest narrow gauge railhead to Lahaul &amp;Spiti. Apart from it Shimla &amp; Chandigarh are two broad gauge railheads for Lahaul &amp; Spiti.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Bhuntar airport in Kullu is the nearest airport for Lahaul &amp; Spiti. From the airport tourists can reach Lahaul &amp; Spiti by private taxi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Lahaul and Spiti are separated by the Kunzum pass. Lahaul and Spiti are connected by a road, but are cut off from each other during some parts of the year due to heavy snowfall.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - LAHAUL &nbsp;AND SPITI - (FAMOUS FOR THUKPA IS A SOUP MADE FROM NOODLES AND SPICES)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(260, 14, 31, 1655, 'Jammu & Kashmir', 'INDIA', 'BANDIPORA', 'spotted-deer-597421_640.jpg', 'spotted-deer-597421_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Bandipora district, also the administrative headquarters of the region, is one of the 22 districts located in the state of J&amp; K. &nbsp;Boasting of its origin in the erstwhile Baramulla district, the scenic landscapes of Bandipora gained the status of an independent district in the year 2007. The beautiful locales of the region are bounded by the district of Baramulla in the south; district of Kupwara in the west; and the districts of Srinagar, Kargil, and Ganderbal in the east. Sumbal Sonawari, Bandipora and Gurez are the three prominent tehsils of Bandipora while the Vidhan Sabha constituencies comprise of Bandipora, Gurez and Sonawari. All these places are an integral part of the Baramulla Lok Sabha constituency. This less visited tourist destination is known for its health resorts such as Zaina Lank, Athwatoo, Chitarnar, Gurez, Bhutoo, and Tulial Valley. Here, there are many beautiful picnic spots that are frequented by locals and tourists alike the chief being Bhutoo Shrine, Athwatoo and Chitarnar.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Although tourists&rsquo; infrastructure in Bandipore is not as highly developed as in some other cities in Jammu and Kashmir, it does have few good hotels and therefore, if decided to spend a few nights here one can do so in comfort.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Srinagar International Airport is just 48 kms away from the Bandipora.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail </strong>- Hamre Railway Station is the closest railway station which about 26 kms from the city center.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Tourists can easily hire cabs from the Jammu or any other place of the Jammu Kashmir to reach Bandipora. Bandipora is easily accessible by Jammu &amp; Kashmir State Road Transport Corporation bus.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - BANDIPORA - {FAMOUS FOR AAB GOSHT IS A STEW MADE FROM LAMB MEAT, CHICKPEAS, WHITE BEANS, ONION, POTATOES, TOMATOES, TURMERIC, AND LIME}</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(261, 14, 31, 1655, 'Jammu & Kashmir', 'INDIA', 'BUDGAM', 'mountain-landscape-640617_6401.jpg', 'landscape-640617_19201.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Established in 1979, Budgam district was earlier an important part of the district of Srinagar. This picturesque region shares its borders with Srinagar and Baramullah in north, Poonch in the south west and Pulwama in the south. Budgam offers a host of scenic locales and boasts of a high percentage of untapped potential in tourism. While in Budgam, tourists like to savour the attractions of Yousmarg, Tosmaidan, Khag, Doodpather and Nilnag. Boasting of the only airport across the Kashmir valley, Budgam is also known for its many bounties at Mt. Tatakuti, and Pehjan. Showcasing the many natural attractions of the region in a treasure trove of lush valleys, meandering Mountain Rivers, green meadows and snow capped peaks this district is definitely worth a visit by one and all. Its many festivals, regional cuisines and traditional art forms warrant a closer look too. Other popular attractions of the district are Khag and Tosamaidan. Tourists from all over come here to see the picturesque little villages which are located at the foothills of the mountains.</p>\r\n', '<p>Fortunately, Budgam has many hotels and guest houses located at convenient locations.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Tourists can easily hire cabs from the Jammu or any other place of the Jammu &amp; Kashmir to reach Budgam.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Airport</strong> - Srinagar International Airport is 14 kms away from the Budgam.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Bus</strong> - There is a well connected bus service from Jammu to Srinagar which takes around 10 hours from Jammu to Srinagar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - Budgam Railway Station is just 15 kms from the city centre.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - BUDGAM - {FAMOUS FOR DHANIWAL KORMA IS A DISH MADE FROM LAMB MEAT COOKED WITH YOGURT ONION, GARLIC, CLOVES, CARDAMOMS, CORIANDER, SAFFRON ; MARCHWANGAN KORMA IS A DISH MADE FROM MEAT OF LAMB/GOAT, CARDAMOMS, CHILLI, TURMERIC, GARAM MASALA, GINGER AND &nbsp;FENNEL}</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '6,8,9,17,18,22,23'),
(262, 14, 31, 1655, 'Jammu & Kashmir', 'INDIA', 'DODA', 'mountain-91385_6402.jpg', 'mountain-91385_1280.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Doda is a district, situated at a height of about 1107 mts above sea level, in Jammu &amp; Kashmir. It received the status of a district in 1948 after it was carved out of the district of Udhampur. The place was named after Deeda, a utensil maker migrant from Multan which now lies in Pakistan. Doda has a varied landscape, including dense forests, high altitude peaks and rich wildlife. This destination is suitable for nature walks, mountaineering, trekking and rock climbing. The major attractions in Doda include Chinta, Bhaderwah and Kishtwar Valley. Kishtwar Valley, situated at a height of 5360 feet, is inhabited by different animal species like leopard, snow deer, Neel gai and musk deer. Doda is also a popular religious site, which is home to the Chandi Mata Temple and Athra Buja Devi Temple. Khani Top, Patnitop, Machail, Sanasar and Sarthal are some of the well known tourist spots that can be easily accessed from Doda.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are different types of hotels in Doda available for families, lovers, kids, and friends and especially for newly married couples who are looking for perfect honeymoon destination. Tariff for hotels in Doda starts from Rs. 700/-. Cheap hotels in Doda may provide basic amenities like a private bedroom, colour TV, Telephone, AC, 24 hour front desk and housekeeping staff on call. These hotels are affordable and value for money.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Srinagar Airport is the air base closest to Doda, is situated about 231 kms away. Also known as Sheikh ul Alam Airport, it is well connected to main cities of India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail </strong>- The Railway station at Srinagar is the nearest rail link to Doda, located at a distance of about 220 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Doda is well connected to Jammu and Srinagar by regular bus services. The J&amp;K State Road Transport Corporation bus services are also available for the destination, which are quite reasonable. Tourists can also avail special deluxe buses for Doda.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - DODA - (FAMOUS FOR GOSHTABA IS A DISH MADE FROM MUTTON, KASOORI METHI, POWDER OF( FENNEL, CUMIN, CINNAMON, CORIANDER), ZEERA, CARDAMOMS, BLACK CARDAMOM, &nbsp;CLOVES, ONION, CURD AND EGG)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(263, 14, 31, 1655, 'Jammu & Kashmir', 'INDIA', 'SONAMARG', 'rainbow-1622730_640.jpg', 'rainbow-1622730_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Sonamarg is a town with snow-covered flower laden fields, surrounded by majestic glaciers and serene lakes which cast subtle spells on the visitors. Translating into &#39;the land of gold&#39;, Sonamarg is a picturesque town located in Kashmir valley at an elevation of around 2800 kms from sea level. Bounded by natural beauty, breathtaking glaciers and serene lakes the place is a popular tourist attraction of Jammu &amp; Kashmir. Nilagrad, a colony of the Baltics, is a picturesque location that one can always visit. Sonamarg is the home of many beautiful and serene lakes. Various mountain lakes such as Gangabal, Vishansar, Gadsar, Satsar and Kishansar are situated in and around Sonamarg. Another scenic eye catching lake in Sonamarg also includes Vishansar. Krishnasar Lake, at a height of 3,801mts above sea level, is popular for fishing with beautiful species such as the trouts. Surrounded by snow capped mountains, the city of Sonamarg lies before the Zoji La Pass. The literal meaning of the word Sonamarg is &lsquo;Meadow of Gold&rsquo;. The place received its name because of the fact that during the spring season, it is enveloped with beautiful flowers that look golden. The high mountain peaks also appear golden when the sun rays fall on them. Sonamarg is a perfect destination for travellers who have an interest in adventurous activities such as trekking and hiking. All the important trek routes start from Sonamarg, making it a popular place for trekking. The place is known for its natural beauty, which includes lakes, passes, and mountains. Sonamarg also acts as the base camp for the pilgrims heading towards Amarnath.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Sonamarg being popular tourist destination offers good and wide range of accomodation with all the modern amenities.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Sheikh ul Alam Airport, commonly known as Srinagar Airport is the nearest airport to Sonamarg, which is located at a distance of around 70 kms from Sonamarg. The airport is well connected with important Indian destinations such as Shimla, Chandigarh, Mumbai, and Delhi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail </strong>- The nearest railhead to Sonamarg is Nowgam Railway Station, also known as Srinagar Railway Station. It located at a distance of 70 kms from Sonamarg but it is not well connected with the rest of the Indian rail network. Jammu Tawi Railway Station is the nearest major rail link to Sonamarg, which is well connected with all the important Indian cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Sonamarg is well connected with nearby places such as Srinagar and Jammu via buses. Tourists can avail J&amp;K State Road Transport Corporation bus services to reach Sonamarg from Jammu and Srinagar. Special luxury buses are also available for the destination.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- To travel around in the town, buses are the best option as they have good frequency inside the city. But if wanting to explore the city at leisure, one can opt for a tanga ride a horse carriage.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SONAMARG - {FAMOUS FOR MATSCHGAND IS A DISH MADE FROM MINCED LAMB MEATBALLS IN SPICY RED GRAVY ; MUJ GAAD IS A DISH MADE FROM FISH WITH RADISH ; SYOON OLAV IS A DISH PREPARED FROM MEAT WITH POTATOES COOKED IN GRAVY ; KAANTI IS A SNACK MADE WITH LAMB PIECES IN RED HOT GRAVY}</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(264, 14, 31, 1655, 'Jammu & Kashmir', 'INDIA', 'KATHUA', 'diya-1782403_640.jpg', 'diya-1782403_1280.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Bounded by three rivers and sharing borders with neighbouring Pakistan, Kathua in Jammu and Kashmir is an important military base of our country. The largest town in Jammu and Kashmir, Kathua is also one of the popular tourist destinations here. Bani, an ideal location with lush green landscape and dense forest are a picture perfect dream location for trekking enthusiast. Well equipped with trekking gear and other trekking facilities, the adventurous minded people love it here. Chandel Bhoond and Banjal are the other locations that are worth a visit. Spend a leisure day with family at Dream, a recreational park, truly portraying its name. Soak up the pleasant atmosphere of this beautiful picnic spot spending the day indulging in water sports like boating, rafting etc., or just lazily enjoying the time with loved ones. Kathua is a district of Jammu &amp; Kashmir, located at a distance of about 88 kms from Jammu. Legend has it that about 2000 years ago, Jodh Singh of the Andotra Dynasty, who was a popular Rajput King, settled here along with his three sons. All the three sons founded three small towns namely, Taraf Manjali, Taraf Tajwal, and Taraf Bhajwal. Together these three towns were known as Kathai by local people and eventually, Kathai became Kathua.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kathua is a hidden gem in the valley of Jammu and Kashmir. This place is gaining momentum in attracting travellers from all around the world. Being a historical place, it is visited by historians as well as adventurist people. To accommodate such travellers, there are many small to medium sized hotels located in the city of Kathua. These hotels are well established with basic amenities along with excellent accommodating facilities to satisfy every individual coming to this region.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Tourists can reach Kathua by road as well, they can opt cabs from Jammu, Pathankot, Chandigarh as well for Kathua.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Airways</strong> - Nearest airport is Pathankot airport and Jammu airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Bus</strong> - Governement bus service is well connected to Kathua tourists can hire buses from Pathankot and Jammu as well.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - Kathua has its own station most of the trains have a halt of around 5 minutes at Kathua railway station which has a distance of around 7 kms from Kathua city centre.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(265, 14, 31, 1655, 'Jammu & Kashmir', 'INDIA', 'KISHTWAR', 'saffron-215932_640.jpg', 'saffron-215932_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kishtwar is popularly known as &lsquo;The Land of Saffron and Sapphire&rsquo; Saffron of purest quality is produced in the iron rich soil at Pochhal, Matta, Lachdayaram and Hidyal. The Padder area produces world class Pine nuts called chilgoza which is a delicacy and costly dry fruit. In Marwah, Chatroo, Mughalmaidan and Bounjwah Tehsils wall nut production of best quality walnuts in thousands of tons is recorded. Besides Walnut the Marwah Tehsil produces thousands of tons of Kidney Beans which are the cash crop of the area. At Rakna palmar there is of Zain Shah Sahab. Kishtwar has also the holy Hindu pilgrimage sites of Athara Bhuja Devi temple, Chandi Mata temple and Asthadash bhuja Sathal Mata Temple. Every year the pilgrimage is arranged for Machail yatra a mega event attended by more than hundred thousand people from all over the country. The annual sarthal yatra is also attended by thousands of devotees. The rural households are also abundantly gifted by nature through cash crops of eatable mushrooms and Morchilla called guchhi in local language. Kishtwar serves as the base camp for trekking and mountaineering to various mountain peaks like Sickle Moon, Crooked Finger, Eiger, Brammah-I, etc. Nagseen, Sarthal, Dachhan, Paddar, Chowgan, Shrine of Shah Asrar are the key attractions of Kishtwar&rsquo;s sightseeing. Despite having immense potential for tourism, Kishtwar is one of the least visited places in Kashmir.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Local hotels at cheap rates are available.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Kishtwar is linked with other places of the state like Jammu, Udhampur, Doda, Srinagar, etc by National Highway 1B. Private and J&amp;KSRTC operated bus services are available. One can also hire private taxi/share taxi from Jammu, Udhampur and Srinagar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The Jammu Tawi is the nearest major railway station that is well connected with all major cities in India including southern railways and northeast frontier railways. At a distance of 164 kms, Udhampur is another nearest railways station.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The most nearest airport to Kishtwar is Jammu. It receives regular flights from Delhi, Srinagar, Leh and Jaipur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Being a small village, it is mostly travelled on foot. Tourists can even hire taxis on hourly or daily basis.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - KISHTWAR - {FAMOUS FOR AMBAL IS A DISH MADE FROM PUMPKIN, TAMARIND PASTE, JAGGERY, POWDERED, METHI DANA, GINGER, RED CHILLIES AND TURMERIC POWDER ; PATISA OR SOAN PAPDI IS A DESSERT MADE FROM GRAM FLOUR, PLAIN FLOUR (MAIDA), GHEE, SUGAR, MILK AND CARDAMOM SEEDS}</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(266, 14, 31, 751, 'Punjab', 'INDIA', 'PATIALA', 'gurudwara-621065_640.jpg', 'gurudwara-621065_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Patiala is the third largest city in Southeast Punjab and is located at an elevation of 250 metres above sea level. The city, built by Sardar Lakhna and Baba Ala Singh, was fortified by Maharaja Narendra Singh (1845-1862). It is the administrative capital of the Patiala District and is dotted with ramparts and ten gates. Patiala is also known as the &lsquo;city of newspapers&rsquo; and is the second media hub of the state of Punjab. The famous printing press of Munshi Nawal Kishore was also established here in the 19th century. The city is also famous for being the home of Hindustani classical music, known by the name of Patiala Gharana. Some popular terminologies are also associated with this city like turban, paranda, Patiala peg and others. Patiala was a princely state of Punjab Province during the British Rule, which was later ruled by the Sidhu Dynasty. Today the city is walled with some popular gateways like Darshani Gate, Lahouri Gate, Nabha Gate, Samana Gate and many more. The establishment of Netaji Subhash National Institute of Sports also made Patiala popular as a sports hub. Patiala experiences extremely hot summers but its winters are not very cold. This is why there is a large tourist turnover in the city between the months of October and March. Patiala is also famous for its colourful clothes and dresses.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Hotels and Resorts are easily available here in Patiala. Most of the low budget hotels are situated near the bus and railway station while mid budget ones are all over the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- The Chandigarh Airport is the nearest to Patiala, which is approximately 60 kms away. Cabs are easily available from this airport to reach the city. The place is connected to all the major cities of the country including Delhi, Chennai, Mumbai and Bangalore by regular flights.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail </strong>- The city has a railway station that is connected to several destinations within the state as well as the country. Tourists can catch trains from Mumbai, Chandigarh and Delhi as these cities provide regular commuting facility.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Reaching Patiala from other states of India by road is quite convenient through National Highway 1. It lies at a distance of around 238 kms from Delhi, which is connected by regular state and private buses. It is also connected by buses to prominent cities in Punjab like Chandigarh and Amritsar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Rickshaws - both manual and autos are the easiest modes of travel.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - KABABCHI, LOCATED AT BHUPINDRA ROAD, CIVIL LINES - (FAMOUS FOR NORTH INDIAN FOOD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - CHAWLA, &nbsp;LOCATED AT NATIONAL HIGHWAY 64, OPPOSITE PUNJABI UNIVERSITY, URBAN ESTATE - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN BIRYANI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - NAGPAL RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT NEAR FOUNTAIN CHOWK, NEW LAL BAGH - (FAMOUS FOR PANEER BHURJI AND MESSI ROTI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - GOPALS SWEETS, LOCATED AT &nbsp;LEELA BHAWAN, BANK COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR RAWA MASALA DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - BABA CHICKEN, LOCATED AT 21 NUMBER RAILWAY CROSSING FLYOVER, MANSHAHIA COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR BUTTER CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - KOHLI SWEETS, LOCATED AT MAIN CHOWK, TRIPURI TOWN - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA AND CHEESE CHILLY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - SADHU RAM, LOCATED AT LAHORI GATE - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n8 - BOMBAY MAHARASHTRIAN PAV BHAJI, LOCATED AT 22 NUMBER RAILWAY FLYOVER, LEELA BHAWAN, BANK COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR PAV BHAJI)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(267, 14, 31, 1653, 'Uttarakhand', 'INDIA', 'PAURI GARHWAL', 'forest-1808520_640.jpg', 'forest-1808520_1280.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Pauri Garhwal is a paradise that showcases the varied colours of nature all packed in to this one place. From snow covered Himalayan peaks and thick cover of lush green forests to deep rooted culture of the place and warm hearted people, this place oozes beauty and charm in every aspect. Perched at an altitude of 1814 mts above the sea level, Pauri also serves as the headquarters to the district by the same name. It also houses many temples but what fascinates the visitors the most is the sunset here. Ending with the hues of pinks and purple, this most magnificent sight of sunset enthrals everyone with its stunning fusion of colours with the bang of bright orange. Situated on the northern slopes of Kandoliya Hills, visit this beautiful place for an unforgettable experience. Tourists can also enjoy panoramic views of the snow capped mountains, namely Bandarpunch, Jonli, Gangotri group, Nandadevi, Trishul, Chaukhamba, Ghori Parvat, Hathi Parvat, Swargarohini, Jogin Group, Thalaiya-Sagar,Kedarnath, Sumeru, and Neelkanth. The Alaknanda and Nayar are the prominent rivers of the district.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Pauri Garhwal offers many budget accommodations with all the basic facilities and amenities. It also houses few luxury hotels and mid range guest houses to match the taste of all kind of tourists.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air </strong>- There is no airport in the Pauri District; the Jolly Grant Airport of Dehradun serves as the nearest airbase located at a distance of 155 kms from the district.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Rail </strong>- The nearest railway station is located in Kotdwara at a distance of 80 kms from Pauri. This railway station is well connected to major cities of the country by regular trains.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Road </strong>- Tourists can reach Pauri on road by convenient bus services. Public and private owned buses ply between Pauri and Rishikesh. Towns like Hardwar, Dehradun and Mussoorie also offer bus services to Pauri.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Buses are the best way to travel in Pauri. Cabs are also available.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(268, 14, 31, 1656, 'Nagaland', 'INDIA', 'PEREN', 'forest-682003_640.jpg', 'forest-682003_1280.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Nagaland is one of the most scenic states in the country, but if there is a place in the state where one still find virgin and untouched forests it is the district of Peren. The inhabitants of this place have preserved the forests religiously which makes it one of biggest attractions in the state. It is bounded by Assam and Dimapur district on the west, district of Kohima in the east and the state of Manipur on the south. The town of Peren which is also the district headquarter is a paradise for the nature lovers. The town which is located on a hill top offer a bird eye view of the neighbouring states of Assam and Manipur. Forming a part of the Barail ranges Peren district has been blessed by Mother Nature. Here in this district one will come across rich and dense vegetation and gushing rivers and different species of animals and birds. The rich vegetation costs of sub tropical mixed forest. The cane and bamboo trees form most of the forest cover along with pine, eucalyptus and different varieties of wild orchid. The district is also rich in mineral resources though these haven&rsquo;t been explored on a large scale.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>There isn&#39;t a whole variety of hotels. The few lodges are quite decent and very reasonable.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - There is no airport in the town of Peren. Dimapur Airport serves as the perfect gateway to this place and is located 71 kilometres from the town.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail</strong> - There are no railway stations in the district of Peren. Dimapur Railway Station which is located 77 kilometres away and serves as an important link to the rest of the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Shuttles and taxis are easily available from Dimapur airport to Peren.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', '');
