(269, 14, 31, 739, 'Haryana', 'INDIA', 'BHIWANI', 'old-man-1145469_640.jpg', 'old-man-1145469_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Widely known as the City of Temples or Choti Kashi, Bhiwani is a beautiful town of Haryana. Created in 1972, Bhiwani district has played an important role in the politics of Haryana and has given three Chief Ministers to the state. Bhiwani was founded by a Rajput King, Neem Singh and he named the city after his wife&rsquo;s name Bhani. Later on, Bhani was changed to Bhiwani. It has been an important centre of commerce from the time of the Mughals. The city had played a major role in the struggle for independence. Among other famous personalities, the city is a hometown to three of Haryana&#39;s chief ministers: Banarsi Dass Gupta, Bansi Lal and Hukum Singh. Pioneer leaders of the city like Neki Ram, Ram Kumar, Uma Sharma, Gokul Chand, Fateh Chand, K.A. Desai and Babu Gupta actively participated in Satyagraha of Bardoli. Bhiwani City Guide is incomplete without a mention of its rich heritage. It is indeed a remarkable place having high historical and religious values. The place is also famous for housing one of the 12 holy Jyotirlinga shrines in India. The city also excels in sports. It has always been a centre of school for boxing. Almost all of the members of the Indian Boxing Squad came from SAI hostel in Bhiwani.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">To cater to a huge number of travellers in the city, there are numerous establishments found in the city which offers wide range of hospitality. Accommodations in Bhiwani are highly important for people coming in the city who have to halt here for few days. Bhiwani is a well diversified city and has many accommodation options to solve the residing problem of travellers. These travellers can choose accommodations according to their suitability of space, luxury along with the size of budget.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Bhiwani is 120 kms away from Delhi. There are so many transports to ply Bhiwani easily. It is well connected to all the cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest airport is Indira Gandhi International Airport in New Delhi having distance 120 kilometres away from Bhiwani.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Bus </strong>- Buses frequently ply from several places to Bhiwani.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train -</strong> There are so many tracks to connect Bhiwani direct by trains. Bhiwani has its own Railway station.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - VATIKA BAR AND FOOD RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT HOUSING BOARD COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR CHILLY MUSHROOM)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - &nbsp;CHATORI GALI, LOCATED AT OPPOSITE CIVIL HOSPITAL, STATION ROAD, RAILWAY COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR PANI PURI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - DAAWAT CHICKEN, LOCATED AT BHIWANI-HANSI ROAD, NEAR NEHRU PARK, HANSI GATE - (FAMOUS FOR BUTTER CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - KULDEEP HOTDOG CORNER, LOCATED AT BAJRANG BALI COLONY, OPP INDIAN OIL PETROL PUMP, ROSTAK ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR HOTDOG)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - PIZZA TREAT, LOCATED AT GHANSHYAM JALAN ROAD, KRISHNA COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - KABAB &#39;N&#39; CURRY, LOCATED AT JAGAT COLONY, VIJAY NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR TANDOORI CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - PYARELAL HALWAI, LOCATED AT OLD ANAJ MANDI, BHAGGANPURI - (FAMOUS FOR MATTAR PANEER)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n8 - LAKSHMI BIKANER MISTHAN BHANDAR, LOCATED AT SH 14, NAYA BAZAR, HOUSING BOARD COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR DHOKLA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>9 - OM SWEETS CORNER THE OLD SHOP, LOCATED AT 171/4, MAL GODAM RD, KRISHNA COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>10 - GANESH MISTHAN BHANDAR, LOCATED AT MEHAM GATE, MEHAM ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR PANIPURI AND VARITIES OF SWEETS)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(270, 14, 31, 739, 'Haryana', 'INDIA', 'FATEHABAD', 'old-man-1145467_640.jpg', 'old-man-1145467_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Fatehabad is a city in the Fatehabad district in Haryana. It is believed that Aryans first settled on the banks of the rivers Saraswati and Drishadvati and then gradually expanded their base to Hisar and Fatehabad. Fatehabad also finds mention in Puranas which say that it was part of the Nanda Empire. The discovery of Ashoka pillars at Fatehabad also shows that it was part of the Maurayan Empire. Excavations carried out here by the Archaeological Survey of India have revealed interesting finds that throw light on ancient India&rsquo;s culture and heritage. The modern town of Fatehabad was founded by Firuz Shah Tughlak in the 14th century. He named it Fatehabad after his son Fateh Khan. During the Mughal regime, this area was considered as one of the most important Kingdoms. There is a beautiful mosque known as Humayun mosque at Fatehabad. It is believed that the Mughal emperor visited it when he was passing through the town after his defeat against Sher Shah Suri. This well constructed fort town bears connection to the Harappan era too. The district Fatehabad was a part of Nanda Empire, according to Puranas. This district also was a part of Mauryan Empire, which was discovered from the Ashokan pillars at Fatehabad.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There is a myriad of options for accommodating the tourists in the city. For luxurious sojourns there are 5 star hotels and lavish resorts in the city which will mesmerize the tourists with their splendour and state of the art amenities. For those who are looking for affordable accommodation options, there are plenty of budget as well as mid range hotels in the city. During peak season tourists are advised to book these places beforehand.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest airport is the Indira Gandhi Airport in New Delhi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail</strong> - Fatehabad district is well connected with Punjab, Delhi and district Sirsa by broad gauge railway line.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Fatehabad is at a distance of about 48 kms northwest of Hisar on Delhi Hisar Sulemanki road. There is a network of metalled roads, which connects all its villages and towns. National Highway 10 connects Fatehabad with Delhi and Punjab.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - LOVELY SWEET SHOP, LOCATED AT THANA ROAD, DWARKA PURI, B BLOCK, ELLENABAD - (FAMOUS FOR GOLGAPPE AND SAMOSA)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(271, 14, 31, 739, 'Haryana', 'INDIA', 'HISAR', 'texture-1108420_640.jpg', 'texture-1108420_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Situated very close to National Capital Region, Hisar is located in the state of Haryana and is the headquarters of Hisar district. It attracts a lot of tourists and is one of the 21 districts of the state. Hisar is quite popular for its Steel industry, textile industry and automobile industry. It is widely known as &lsquo;The City of Steel&rsquo; because of the presence of large number of steel industries in the area. Hisar was the most important planned centre of Ibrahim Lodi&rsquo;s kingdom when Babur attacked India in 1524-1526. During the British reign, the city was ruled by George Thomas in 1798. It continued up to 1801 when George Thomas was thrown out by the Sikh Maratha French confederacy. The city was established by Firoz Shah Tughlaq as Hisar e Firoza in 1354 AD who ruled from 1351 to 1388 over the Sultanate of Delhi. A trip to Hisar ensures a rich dose of history to all tourists with palaces, mosque, temples and monuments displaying ancient culture at its best. History lovers will get a feel of the Harappan culture at the ruins of Harappan sites very near the Feroz Shah Palace, majestically built fort with an underground chamber and a mosque. Built in memory of his wife, Gujri Rani by Tughlaq, Gujri Mahal is an imposing masterpiece of its time sure to hold the spell bound. Spend a relaxing day with the loved ones at the Jindal Parks, well manicured parks to relax with a display of colourful flowers.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Being a business and trade hub in the region, Hisar facilitates best option for accommodation from luxurious to affordable choices. The hotels in this city facilitate all sorts of desired amenities visitors expect from them for a great and memorable stay. Here are some of the notable hotels in Hisar that make best choice for the visitors to enjoy their stay.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Hisar is well connected by road having 165 kms from Delhi. It is also very well connected to all major cities of the state and neighbouring states too.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The closest airport to Hisar is Indira Gandhi International Airport, Delhi about 174 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Bus</strong> - By HSRTC and private buses Hisar is easily accessible from other major states and cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - Hisar has its own railway station which connects to all major cities and states.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - PAHUJA FAST FOOD &amp; JUICE CORNER, LOCATED AT RED SQUARE MARKET, RAILWAY ROAD, MEHTA NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR PAVBAGI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - SAINI SWEETS, LOCATED AT MEHTA NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR JALEBI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - BISHNOI DHABA, LOCATED AT AGGARWAL COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR KADDHI CHURMA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - ANIL RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT RAILWAY RDOAD RAMPURA MOHALLA, MEHTA NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR CHOLE BHATURE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - SHARMA SWEETS SHOP, LOCATED AT INNER SATROD ROAD, SATROD KHURD&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n6 - GOHANA SWEETS, LOCATED AT OPPOSITE MAIN BUS STAND, NEAR GUJARI MEHAL - (FAMOUS FOR JALEBI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(272, 14, 31, 739, 'Haryana', 'INDIA', 'JHAJJAR', 'india-972746_640.jpg', 'india-972746_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Jhajjar is one of the 21 districts of the state of Haryana state. The district, with its headquarters in Jhajjar town, was carved out of Rohtak district on July 15th, 1997. The town is believed to have been founded by Chhaju as Chhajunagar. The name was later changed to Jhajjar. The second story goes that the name has been derived from Jharnaghar, a natural fountain. A third version has it that it was named Jhajjar, a water vessel, because the surface drainage of the area for miles around runs into the town as into a sink. Jhajjar has much to offer the nature enthusiasts. The Bhindawas bird sanctuary, just about 3 hours from Delhi, is one of the major attractions of the district. Spread over 1074 acres, it attracts more than 35,000 varieties of migratory water birds comprising more than 250 species from various regions of the world. The sanctuary also has a lake which is surrounded by a man made 12 kms embankment to trap the water. Another attraction that deserves a mention is the Archaeological Museum of Gurukul. The museum houses a huge assortment of antique idols and coins brought in from various states of the country including Rajasthan, Haryana, Punjab, Allahabad and Bareli in Uttar Pradesh.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">When on a tour to Jhajjar the various hotels present in the city which can provide with good accommodation along with various facilities. Most of the hotels provide the basic facilities. The tariffs of the hotel differ as per the rooms chosen for staying and the facilities being offered. Many of them have the facility of online booking too.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Jhajjars&rsquo;s road network is excellent which connect all the major cities and states.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest airport is Indira Gandhi Intl Airport, Delhi which is about 55 kms form Jhajjar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Bus </strong>- HSTC, private buses and all state corporation buses are ply frequently from all major cities and states to Jhajjar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train </strong>- Rohtak Railway Station is nearest railway station from Jhajjar which is connected to all the major cities and states.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - DULICHAND SWEETS, LOCATED AT CIRCULAR ROAD, NH 71, BHATTI GATE - (FAMOUS FOR BARFI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - RAMPY&#39;S, LOCATED AT JHAJJAR - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - POMAL SAMOSE WALA, LOCATED AT JHAJJAR - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSAS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - DEVI BARFI BHANDAR, LOCATED AT OPPOSITE SHIBA PANSARI ,MAIN BAZAR - (FAMOUS FOR BARFI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - DRAGON DELIGHTS, LOCATED AT &nbsp;JHAJJAR - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;BRIYANI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n6 - DULICHAND HALWAI SWEETS, LOCATED AT BHATTI GATE&nbsp;- (FAMOUS FOR VARITIES OF KHOYA SWEETS, KHEER AND MALPUA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - CHOTU RAM BAKER&#39;S, LOCATED AT NEAR PUNJABI DHARAMSHLA, MAIN BAZAR - (FAMOUS FOR CAKE, PASTRIES AND COOKIES0</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>8 - DSD PAKODE WALE, LOCATED AT OPPOSITE SHIV MANDIR, JHAJJAR ROAD, DADRI TOYE - (FAMOUS FOR PANEER PAKODAE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>9 - CRUNCHY, LOCATED AT JHAJJAR ROAD, AIRY NAGAR, SAKTI NAGAR, BAHADURGARH - (FAMOUS FOR BURGER)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(273, 14, 31, 739, 'Haryana', 'INDIA', 'JIND', 'man-1700911_640.jpg', 'man-1700911_960_720.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Jind, a district in Haryana takes its name from Jaintapuri, an ancient tirtha which finds mention in the epic Mahabharata. Pandavas built the Jayanti Devi Temple to honour the goddess Jainti, who was regarded as the goddess of victory and success. The town came up around this temple as Jaintapuri which was later known as Jind. Apart from mythology, the antiquity of this district has also been established based on the excavations carried out here. Several pre Harappan, the late Harappan and the painted Grey Ware pottery have been found around the district. Also the mention of its tirthas in the ancient Puranas collaborate the findings. Jind is an important pilgrimage destination and has several religious sites to its credit. Bhuteshvara Templeis dedicated to Lord Shiva who is also called Bhootnath. This temple was built by Raghbir Singh, the ruler of Jind. Jind enjoys all the three seasons, summer, winter and monsoon. Best time to visit Jind is from November to March. Jind is a city of historical and mythological importance. Interestingly, Jind was also one of the first Sikh kingdoms.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Jind gets thousands of visitors each year owing to its cultural, archaeological and religious importance. There are a number of hotels and resorts in Jind where tourists can stay at and it has all the modern facilities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest airport is the Indira Gandhi International Airport in Delhi, which is 145 kms from the city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Jind Railway Station, located on the Northern Railway network, connects the city to Delhi, Patiala, Chandigarh and other major towns of Haryana and other neighbouring states.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Jind is connected by the National Highway 71. In addition, a wide network of metalled roads also connects the city to other cities like Bhiwani, Ambala, Chandigarh, Faridabad, Hisar, Jagadhri and Karnal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - The best modes of transport, in the city are buses and they regularly ply across the length and breadth of the district. Auto rickshaws, taxis and auto rickshaws are also readily available mode of transport in Jind.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - DA PIZZA HUB JIND, LOCATED AT HUDA MARKET, DC COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - RED ROSE VEGETARIAN, LOCATED AT NEAR ARJUN STADIUM, NATIONAL HIGHWAY 71, RANI TALAB - (FAMOUS FOR SOUTH INDIAN FOOD AND ALOO POORI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - BURGERWALA, LOCATED AT KASHI COLONY, JIND-GOHANA ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - JANTA PERA BHANDAR, LOCATED AT PATIALA CHOWK, RAILWAY STATION ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(274, 14, 31, 739, 'Haryana', 'INDIA', 'KAITHAL', 'india-787727_640.jpg', 'india-787727_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Kaithal is a historical city and municipal council in Kaithal district of Haryana. It was once part of Karnal District and later on of Kurukshetra District. On 1st November 1989 it became the headquarters of the Kaithal District of Haryana. The neighbouring cities of Kaithal are Patiala, Kurukshetra, Jind and Karnal. It is located on northwest of the Haryana state. On its northwest boundaries it is attached to Punjab State. Kaithal was previously known as Kapisthal which means &quot;Abode of Kapi&quot;. Kapi is another name of Lord Hanuman. Kaithal is said to be the birthplace of Lord Hanumana. The city has a temple dedicated to Lord Hanumana and named after his mother &quot;Anjani Tila&quot;. Kaithal is believed to be founded by the Pandav Emperor, Yudhisthira of Mahabharata. Various tombs and monuments of medieval era are clearly visible in this part of Haryana. The climate of this place can be largely classified as tropical steppe, semi arid and hot. The summers here are very dry with very hot summer. The winters are very cold and the monsoons are moist and humid. Kaithal has remains of many fort and several Muslim tombs of historic times. The Kaithal fort is among the most famous one. It was used by British rulers to control the entry of trade goods and other items. Tomb of Sheikh Tayyab is another famous attraction of this historic city. It is a 16th century tomb situated in Kaithal city near Railway line.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Kaithal offers many hotels, heritage hotels and dharamshalas for a comfortable stay.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><br />\r\n<strong>By Road </strong>- Kaithal is well connected by road. It is very easy to reach any area of Punjab through this by road. It is directly attached to Delhi, the National capital by bus route 120 kms. There is a direct bus service for Dubawali, Sirsa from here from which one can enter the Rajasthan boundary.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Train </strong>- Kaithal railway station is situated between Kurukshetra and Narwana branch line of railway. It is very easy to reach Delhi very comfortably either from Kurukshetra or Narwana.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air</strong> - Nearest airport to Kaithal is Indira Gandhi International Airport, Delhi which is about 156 kms.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(275, 14, 31, 739, 'Haryana', 'INDIA', 'KARNAL', 'bike-rider-272843_640.jpg', 'bike-rider-272843_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Located in the state of Haryana, Karnal is one of the 21 districts of the state. The city is midway between New Delhi and Chandigarh and is 123 kms from Delhi in north and 136 kms from Chandigarh in south, connected through National Highway NH 1. Karnal City Guide is incomplete without a mention of its rich cultural heritage and industrial significance. The city is home to several world class Research and Development Institutes such as Indian Agricultural Research Institute (IARI), National Bureau of Animal Genetic Resources (NBAGR), Central Soil Salinity Research Institute (CSSRI), National Dairy Research Institute (NDRI), and Directorate of Wheat Research (DWR). Some of the prominent attractions of the city are Karnal Fort, Pukka Pul and Karnal Lake. The original name of the city was Karnalaya and later it changed to Karnal and is named after Karna, the eldest son of Kunti. Hence, the city is also acknowledged as the city of daanvir Karna. The city is believed to have been established by the Kauravas for the king Karna who was the mythological hero and a central figure during the Mahabharata era. This city is also the birthplace of Kalpana Chawla.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Karnal has a lot for deluxe and medium to budget accommodation options with all facilities to make the stay a memorable one. The hotels in Karnal will fulfil all the requirements by providing state of the art amenities within their sprawling premises. The hotels have excellent room services and delectable dining options that will certainly charm the stay.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Road </strong>- Karnal is well connected by road to all the nearby regions in the state and cities. The National Highway NH 1 connects Delhi and Chandigarh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest Airport from Karnal is Chandigarh Airport is well connected to cities and states in the country and worldwide.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Bus </strong>- Karnal is well connected by buses which frequently ply from nearby states as well as cities. Available bus services are HSRTC, private buses and air conditioned buses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - Karnal has its own railway station. It is well connected by rail network to all the nearby regions in the state as well as other places around the state.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - MUNSHIRAM SWEETS, LOCATED AT 241,GURUNANAK PURA, KARNAL - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;KACHORI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - ODEAN SWEETS &amp; RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT OPPOSITE BUS STAND,OLD GT ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR GHEVAR IS A DESERT MADE FROM FLOUR, GHEE, KEWRA, MILK, CLARIFIED BUTTER, SUGAR, ALMONDS, PISTACHIO, SAFFRON, GREEN CARDAMOM)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - GOPAL JI SWEETS, LOCATED AT JUNDLA GATE, KARNAL, NOVELTY CINEMA RD, JATAN MOHALLA - (FAMOUS FOR JALEBI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - ATAM JYOTI SWEETS, LOCATED AT 529, SECTOR 7 - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA,BURGER,NOODLES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - AMBER SWEET &amp; BHOJNALAYA, LOCATED AT GHANTA GHAR CHOWK - {FAMOUS FOR CHOLA BHATURE AND LASSI (BUTTERMILK)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - PARTH SWEETS HOUSE, LOCATED AT NEAR TAXI STAND, INDRI TEHSIL - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA &nbsp;AND TEA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n7 - KEWAL DHABA, LOCATED AT SHOP NO. 8-9, CIVIL HOSPITAL CHOWK - (FAMOUS FOR BUTTER CHICKEN, DAAL FRY AND RAJMAHA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>8 - SNACKS MASTER, LOCATED AT OLD HOUSING BOARD COLONY, SECTOR -13 - (FAMOUS FOR DAL MAKHANI AND PANEER DISHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>9 - PUFFED STUFFED, LOCATED AT SCO 330MUGHAL CANAL, DYAL SINGH COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR PANEER ROLLS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>10 - KALRA SWEETS, LOCATED AT 1377, SECTOR 13 URBAN ESTATE - (FAMOUS FOR PAV BHAJI AND JALEBI)&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(276, 14, 31, 739, 'Haryana', 'INDIA', 'MAHENDERGARH', 'candles-621088_640.jpg', 'candles-621088_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Mahendergarh was earlier known as &#39;Kanaud&#39; because of its association with Kanaudia group of Brahmans. During the middle of the nineteenth century, it came to be known as Mahendergarh. Although the nomenclature of the district is not very old, the archaeological explorations conducted in the region have brought to light late Harappan sites in the Rewari tehsil. However this type of evidence along with Painted Grey Ware, Northern Black Polished Ware and Early Historical Ware has been also gathered from the adjoining districts of Bhiwani and Gurgaon. So far not a single PGW site has come to light in the district, perhaps suggesting the north-eastward migrations of the Aryans from the banks of the Saraswati and the Drisadvati possibly happened due to the drying up of their courses. Most of the sites explored in Mahendergath belong to the late medieval period. The district, it may further be pointed out, might have possibly remained outside the main stream of Aryan culture and hence has not been specifically mentioned in the traditional literature as an independent territorial unit. However, it has been suggested that some of the present streams of the district may be identified with those mentioned in early Vedic literature. Mahendragarh is emerging as the new education hub of Haryana with several high standard schools, like Yaduvanshi Shiksha Niketan and colleges, including engineering colleges and a Central University having come up here. It is also having top class health facilities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">From three to one starred hotels, one will find it all in Mahendergarh based on the budget.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Mahendergarh is well connected to all the major cities and neighbouring states by road.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest airport from Mahendergarh is Indira Gandhi International Airport, Delhi which is about 127 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Bus </strong>- HSTC and Private Buses ply between all other major cities and states.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train </strong>- Mahendergarh has its own railway station which connects all major cities of the state and also all neighbouring states.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - S.K. BURGER, LOCATED AT DEEP CITY COMPLEX NEAR AZAD CHOWCK, SHANKER COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR PASTA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - SAINI RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT SHANKER COLONY, MOHINDERGARH - (FAMOUS FOR FRUITJUICES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - BILLU MISTHAN BHANDAR, LOCATED AT REWARI-KANINA-MAHENDRAGARH RD, KANINA - (FAMOUS FOR GULAB JAMUN, SAMOSA AND PANNER PAKODA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(278, 14, 31, 739, 'Haryana', 'INDIA', 'MEWAT', 'door-1383893_640.jpg', 'door-1383893_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Mewat district was carved from erstwhile Gurgoan and Hathin subdivision of Faridabad district and came into existence on 4th April 2005 as the 20th district of the Haryana State. After the formation of Palwal district, Hathin sub division was transferred to Palwal district. Nuh town is Mewat districts headquarter. Land of the Meos has its genesis in its tribal inhabitants, the Meo tribals, who are agriculturalist. The area is a distinct ethnic and socio cultural tract. The Meos, who trace their roots to the early Aryan immigration into northern India, call themselves Kshatriyas and have preserved their social and cultural traits to a surprisingly large extent, unlike the other tribes of nearby areas. During the regime of the Tughlak dynasty in the 14th century CE, these people embraced Islam but till today, they have maintained their age old distinctive ethno cultural identity. Historically, the region has been extremely turbulent and has been subject to repeated invasions and resultant plundering throughout the post Vedic period, largely due to the situational peculiarity of the area and the non subjugate attitude of the people. The destruction and devastation over the centuries resulted in backwardness and underdevelopment of both the area and its people.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Haryana is no different, boasting of a wide array of comfortable budget hotels. That being said, travelling on a small budget to Haryana no longer means having to sacrifice on comfort the tourism boom that affected all of India has had effects in Mewat as well, where some of the best budget hotels in Haryana are located.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Mewat is well connected to neighbouring states Delhi, Rajasthan and Uttar Pradesh by high frequency bus service run by the Haryana Roadways and other public/private transport. In district Mewat, bus service is the major means of public transport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train </strong>- The nearest railway junction to the town is Gurgaon located at a distance of 45 kms which is one of the oldest Railway Station situated on the Delhi Rewari Jaipur Railway line route. It is at a distance of about 3 km from main old Gurgaon City.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Air </strong>- The Nearest airports are Indira Gandhi International Airport, New Delhi which is 64 kms and is well connected to domestic and international destinations.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(279, 14, 31, 739, 'Haryana', 'INDIA', 'PALWAL', 'old-man-1145469_6401.jpg', 'old-man-1145469_6402.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Palwal, the cotton hub is situated in the Palwal district of Haryana. It is situated 60 kms away from Delhi. During the reign of the Pandavas, there was a demon named Palwasur after whom the place is named. The mention of Palwal can be found in the Mahabharata as a part of the Pandava kingdom of Indraprastha. The demon Palwasur was killed by Lord Krishna&#39;s brother Balaram. It was also the place of king Vikramaditya. During the British rule, it belonged to both the Punjab and Gurgaon region. Palwal is historically significant as many freedom fighters participated in the independence movement of India. Every year a festival called Baldev Chatt Ka Mela is organized here. A temple dedicated to Balaram called the Dauji temple is also there. This temple is located near the Municipal Chowk of Palwal. Palwal is one of the most important producers of cotton in the country. Cotton from here is supplied all over the country.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The city of Palwal is one of the most fascinating towns of the state of Haryana as it is a peaceful city. Thus, this place also attracts a number of tourists and thereby, there are quite a few hotels and guests houses, which prove to be ideal places of accommodation for visitors.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest airport is Indira Gandhi International Airport, Delhi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail</strong> - Palwal is one of the railway stations in Haryana that come under the category of big stations. Trains from Palwal to almost all major cities of India are available.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road </strong>- As it is situated on National Highway 2, buses are available on a regular basis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Public transportation by buses being the major means in the city and there are three major bus stands at Palwal, Hodal and Hathin. To travel to even nearer places, for people who either do not have a car or wish not to drive on their own for a trip, can avail the various taxi and cab services available in city Palwal.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - GOGIA&#39;S SNACKS BAR, LOCATED AT &nbsp;AGRA CHOWK, NEW COLONY ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - PASHI, LOCATED AT JAWAHAR NAGAR, CAMP MARKET - (FAMOUS FOR CHOLE BHATURE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - SHYAM DHABA PALWAL,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT NH2 ADJOING ADVANCE INSTITUTE OF TECNOLOGY AND MANAGEMENT AND SRIRAM COLLEGE, VILLAGE SRI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR PANEER CHILLY AND DAL TADKA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - RICH AND RICH, LOCATED AT OLD GT RD, DHARAM NAGAR COLONY, HOUSING BOARD COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR CHOWMIEN)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '6,8'),
(280, 14, 31, 735, 'Chandigarh', 'INDIA', 'PANCHKULA', 'sadhu-1166066_640.jpg', 'sadhu-1166066_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Punchkula is one of the planned cities of India and a satellite city of Chandigarh. One of the five census towns of Panchkula district, Panchkula shares its border with Mohali in Punjab. Chandimandir Cantonment, the esteemed Headquarter of Indian Army resides in Panchkula. The name Panchkula originates from five irrigation canals or kuls as they are locally known. These canals take water from Ghaggar River which gets distributed to the regions around like Nada Sahib and Manasa Devi. The canals are extremely useful to the local people and are maintained by the villagers. People residing in Panchkula mostly speak in Punjabi and Hindi. Haryanvi is the state language. Metro route is being planned for better convenience of people. Panchkula experiences sub tropical continental monsoon climate. Summers are hot; winters are cool and good rainfall in monsoons. October and November is the ideal time to explore Panchkula. The city has acquired its name from the five irrigation canals or can say &lsquo;kuls&rsquo; which means &lsquo;panch kuls&rsquo; or &lsquo;five canals&rsquo; in common terms. Panchkula travel guide talks about its physical aspects as the city is bounded by Himachal Pradesh in the northern region and eastern part is covered with Punjab. The western part is covered by the Union Territory of Chandigarh and the south is covered with Ambala district. Panchkula district shares its borders with famous cities like Chandigarh, Mohali, Solan and Ambala.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Panchkula city houses numerous budget hotels and it has three star hotels which offer great accommodation services to its guests. The city has a number of heritage hotels which are located in the proximity of the railway station and the bus terminal as well. The rooms offered by the hotels are of diverse categories which include standard rooms, deluxe rooms, executive rooms and suites that are offered at economical and budget friendly prices. The hotels are well equipped with scores of contemporary amenities which are available in all the rooms which are quite spacious and offer comfort to the guest.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Road </strong>- It is well connected by road network which connects all neighbouring major cities and states.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest airport is the Chandigarh Airport which is well connected with all the major states and cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Bus </strong>- Panchkula is easily accessible by bus service to all the major cities and states.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train </strong>- It doesn&#39;t have its own railway station. Nearest one is Chandigarh railway station which is connected to all the major cities and states.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - CHAWLA FAMILY RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT SWASTIK VIHAR, MANSA DEVI COMPLEX, SECTOR-5 - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN AND MEAT CURRY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - SHIV KARTHIK RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT DSS 252, ROAD, SECTOR 20 - (FAMOUS FOR SOUTH INDIAN FOOD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - ZAIKA, LOCATED AT SCO 69, GROUND FLOOR, SWASTIK VIHAR, MDC, SECTOR 5 - (FAMOUS FOR JALEBI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - PANNA SWEETS, LOCATED AT MAIN BAZAR, MANIMAJRA - (FAMOUS FOR BREAD ROLL)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - SAI SWEETS, LOCATED AT &nbsp;SCO-1102-03, HIMALAYA MARG, 17G, 22B, SECTOR 22 - (FAMOUS FOR CHANNA BHATURA AND MASALA TEA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - KRISHAN CHAT BHANDAR, LOCATED AT BOOTH NO 120, S C F 39/2, SECTOR 18-D - {FAMOUS FOR GOL-GAPPA (PANI PURI)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - &nbsp;BANSAL AMRITSAR FOOD STREET, LOCATED AT SCF 3, IT PARK ROAD, MDC SECTOR 4&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; - (FAMOUS FOR KULCHA IS A TYPE OF FLATBREAD MADE FROM MAIDA FLOUR, STUFFED WITH THE FILLINGS OF, PANEER, POTATOES, VEGETABLES, ONION AND EATEN WITH CHOLE)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '6,8,18,25'),
(281, 14, 31, 1656, 'Nagaland', 'INDIA', 'PHEK', 'bike-rider-272843_640.jpg', 'bike-rider-272843_640.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Nagaland is one of those unexplored parts of India that has so much stored within its hills, valleys and plains that a single visit would make one want to keep coming back again and again. Phek is among the closely guarded secrets of Nagaland where natural beauty and cultural enthusiasm, all mingle to become one. The town of Phek which falls under the district with the same name is located in the south eastern part of Nagaland. The district shares its boundaries with Myanmar in the east, the state of Manipur in the south, Kohima district in the west and Zunheboto and Tuensang districts in the north. Previously Phek was a part of the Kohima district, and it is located 145 kms from the city of Kohima. Phek means &#39;watch tower&#39; and is derived from the word &lsquo;Phekrekedze&rsquo;. The main inhabitants of Phek are the Chakhesangs and Pochurys while the spoken language here is the Tenyidie and Nagamese. Interestingly, Chakhesangs is not the name of one tribe but a combination of three sub tribes Chokri, Khezha and Sang.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Really affordable hotels and guest houses are available.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The Phek district doesn&rsquo;t have its own airport. However, the airport at Dimapur serves for this south eastern district too.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail</strong> - The Dimapur railway station serves as the nearest rail route for Phek. Located at a distance of 189 kms from Phek, it is a convenient route for a traveller.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Since Phek is solely dependent on the road for communications, this is the cheapest way to reach this Nagaland district. Regular buses from all over Nagaland including Kohima and Dimapur will take the visitors to Phek easily. Apart from the state transport buses, there are several private buses too. Tourists can also book a tourist bus to reach Phek.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Travelling by car is the only option but the roads are really poor.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(282, 14, 31, 1653, 'Uttarakhand', 'INDIA', 'PITHORAGARH', 'amritsar-trip-bg1.jpg', 'mountain-91385_640.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Pithoragarh is a district in the state of Uttarakhand and serves as a gateway to the mighty Himalayan ranges. It is located in the beautiful Soar Valley and is bordered by the Almora District in the north. The Kali River separates it in the east from the neighbouring country Nepal. Most of the ancient temples and forts were constructed here during the reign of the Pal and Chand dynasties. In the 15th century, the region was controlled by the Brahm Kings for a short period. Later, the kings of the Chand Dynasty restored their rule and reigned till the British took over. Kumaoni is the language spoken by the tribes living here. The region is rich in natural resources like limestone, copper, magnesium, and slate. It is surrounded by lush green coniferous, sal, chir, and oak forests. The region is home to the Himalayan chamois, sambar and tiger, along with several birds and reptiles. Various churches, mission schools, and buildings were built during the British rule. Tourist planning to explore Pithoragarh can visit the Kapileshwar Mahadev Temple, which is dedicated to the Hindu Lord Shiva.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Pithoragarh, although a small town, has good number of hotels and guest houses to match the travellers varied taste. Most of the accommodations are economical budget with few resorts in its bag. With good service, food and surroundings, overall stay in Pithoragarh is a good experience.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- The Pantnagar Airport is the nearest air base to Pithoragarh, which is located at a distance of 250 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail </strong>- The Tanakpur Railway Station is the nearest railhead, located at a distance around 150 kms from Pithoragarh. This railway station is well connected to major cities of North India. Taxis are available from this railway station to Pithoragarh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Tourists can reach the destination by buses. The state owned buses connect the town of Pithoragarh to different places like Kathgodam, Almora, and Haldwani.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Commuting within the town of Pithoragarh is quite easy. Being a small urban town, getting a taxi is the best option. Make sure to avoid visiting the place during rainy season as frequent landslides can spoil the trip. The town is quite refreshing during the summers while winters offer some breathtaking views.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - KUMAR SWEETS, LOCATED IN PITHORAGARH - (FAMOUS FOR JALEBI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - SELAL CHOWMIN CENTRE, LOCATED AT LINK ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR CHOWMIEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - JAGDAMBA RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT GANGOLIHAT TIMTA PITHORAGARH ROAD, RAN KOTE UPRETI - (FAMOUS FOR VARITIES OF CAKES AND SWEETS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - RUCHI SWEETS, LOCATED AT GANDHI CHOWK - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;CHOLE SAMOSE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - MEGHNA, LOCATED AT GANDHI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR SOUTH INDIAN FOOD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - SATKAR SWEETS N RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT SIMALGAIR BAZAR - (FAMOUS FOR BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(283, 14, 31, 1655, 'Jammu & Kashmir', 'INDIA', 'POONCH', 'vietnam-1714359_6401.jpg', 'vietnam-1714359_1280.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Poonch is a remote district in the state of Jammu &amp; Kashmir, which is also known as &lsquo;Mini Kashmir&rsquo;. Located amidst beautiful nature, the district of Poonch is enclosed by the Actual Line of Control (ALC) from three sides. The region of Poonch is of great historical significance as it has been ruled by several local and foreign rulers. Hiuen Tsang, the famous Chinese traveller crossed through Poonch during 6th century. He later wrote that this place was famous for good horses, graphics, and fine tea called Musloom. Poonch was ruled by Mr. Nar, the self declared King of Poonch, who was a horse trader, during 850 AD. Later in 1596 AD, Siraj-ud-din was made the King of Poonch by the Mughal Emperor Jahangir. Then during 1798 AD, Rooh-ullah-Sangu, who was a Gujjar leader started to rule the entire region.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Make the most of a vacation by relishing the comforts and services of budget accommodations its decent arrangement and wonderful services guarantee a convenient stay.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\n<strong>By Air </strong>- Jammu Airport also called Satwari Airport is the closest domestic air base located at a distance of around 234 kms to Poonch. The airport is well connected to important places in India such as Mumbai, Goa, Jaipur, Delhi, Chandigarh, Leh, and Srinagar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail </strong>- Jammu Tawi Railway Station is the closest rail link to Poonch. It is well connected with some of the major Indian destinations such as Chennai, Howrah, Bangalore, Delhi, and Trivandrum.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Regular buses for Poonch are available from Jammu. Tourists can also opt for J&amp;K State Road Transport Corporation buses from Jammu, which are quite reasonable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Many local buses including Matadors and city bus services run within the city. They might take longer time but this is the most economical way of exploring the city. For a comfortable and private option, one may hire a cab or a taxi from the many private taxi vendors. For covering shorter distances, one can hire a cycle-rickshaw or an auto-rickshaw.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - POONCH - {FAMOUS FOR KABARGAH IS A DISH MADE FROM MUTTON AND COOKED IN MILK AND SPICES, AND WRAPPED IN GRAM FLOUR BATTER}</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(284, 14, 31, 1657, 'Chhattisgarh', 'INDIA', 'BEMETARA', 'lily-1646423_640.jpg', 'lily-1646423_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Bemetara is a city under Bemetara district in Chhattisgarh. It came into existence on January 14, 2012 when Balod and Bemetara were separated from Durg district to become the 21st and 22nd districts of Chhattisgarh. Divided into 21 wards, this district is regarded as the largest town in the state when it comes to the land and population. The city of Bemetara is surrounded by varied geographical features like Shivnath River to the east, dense forests to the south, Maikal Hills to the north-west, the Chota Nagpur Plateau to the north and the Deccan Plateau to its southern side. Furthermore, the district is located on the total area of 2854.81 sq km and it shares its borders with seven other districts of Chhattisgarh and they are Durg, Baloda Bazaar, Bilaspur Kawardha, Rajnandgaon and Mungeli. Bemetara is well connected to the other major cities of Chhattisgarh state through different ways of transportation, railways and roadways, in particular. The name of Bemetara was derived from Queen Vyomtara who ruled this area for a long time. The district of Bemetara has a long historical background. According to some studies, the entire area of Durg district including Bemetara was under the rule of Mauryan Emperor Ashoka. In the year 1762, the area came under the Marathas which further captured by King Bhosle in the year 1853. Bemetara is located in proximity to the centre of a large plain and thus the climate in this region is tropical wet and dry. The region experiences moderate climate for most of the periods except the months of March to June, when it remains very hot.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are descent amoumt of Hotels, Resorts, and Lodges &amp; Guest Houses in Bemetara.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest airport to Bemetara is Raipur airport, which is 61 kms away from Bemetara city centre.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train -</strong> The nearest railway station to Bemetara is Bhatapara railway station which is 42 kms away from Bemetara city centre.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road -</strong> National Highway 12A is passes through this district that connects the state capital Raipur to Jabalpur city. However, this region is also placed near to two state highways in which the first one is passing from Bemetara to Durg and the second one is from Kumhari to Mungeli.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport</strong> - The local transportation here is in the form of hand rickshaws and auto rickshaws.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - BEMETARA - {FAMOUS FOR DEHRORI IS A SWEET DISH MADE FROM RICE, CURD, GHEE, SUGAR AND CARDAMOM POWDER}</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '');
