(285, 14, 31, 1657, 'Chhattisgarh', 'INDIA', 'BILASPUR', 'rice-1121001_640.jpg', 'rice-1121001_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Widely known as the Rice Bowl of India, Bilaspur is located in the state of Chhattisgarh and is the second most highly developed town in India. Situated on a ridge 860 ft above sea level, it is positioned on the banks of River Arpa. It is 111 kms away from state&rsquo;s capital towards the north east of Chhattisgarh. Bilaspur is visited majorly by locals of the state as well as tourists from all over the country. The place is known all over the world for its several different varieties of Mangoes, Saris, Aromatic Doobraj rice, Handloom woven Kosa Silk and also for its rich and diverse culture. It is very famous for its captivating sightseeing places which attract the tourists from all over the world. Some of the popular and must see attractions of the city include Khadia Dam, Kutaghat Dam, Markandeya Ji and Shri Naina Devi Temple etc. Bilaspur is the second largest and third most populous district of Chattisgarh. It is the hub of electric power generation in India. Bilaspur is one of the places which generate highest revenues through railways. Chhattisgarh State High Court is situated here. The name Bilaspur originates from Bilasa, fisherwomen of the 17th century. This place was at once den of few fishermen. Later Maratha invaded whose rule died heirless with the East India Company coming into prominence.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">While traveling to Bilaspur tourists do not have to worry about staying as there are numerous accommodation options available in the city. Tourists have to choose from the wide range of staying option available. They can opt to stay either in luxury hotel or budget hotel depending upon the budget.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Bilaspur Airport is located at Chakarbhatta though not served by regular flights. It is 10 kms from Bilaspur. Raipur is the nearest airport active airport situated 115 kms from this place.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Bilaspur railway station is the zonal head of South East Central Railway. It is thus the busiest station of Chhattisgarh and the hub of regional railway. It is the fourth busiest junction in India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - NH-200 connects Raipur and Raigarh with Bilaspur. Kolkata and Mumbai are connected by National Highways. Ambikapur and Varanasi are connected by NH-111. State Highways running through Bilaspur connect other states of India. Bus and taxis are available for internal transportation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - For local transportation the most common mode is Auto rickshaws and man powered cycle Rickshaws. Horse drawn Carriage or Tangas and city buses are also popular mode of transportation. Recently the city administration has started a city bus service which is available on major routes. City transport is managed by Bilaspur City Bus Ltd.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - MANOJ SWEETS &amp; NAMKEEN, LOCATED AT MUNGELI NAKA GROUND, MUNGELI ROAD, KUDUDAND, MANGLA - (FAMOUS FOR POHA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - MAOSAJI SWEETS, LOCATED AT GOLE BAZAR - (FAMOUS FOR RASGULLAS AND KAJU BARFI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - MANOJ BAKERY, LOCATED AT JAGMAL CHOWK - (FAMOUS FOR CAKES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - HARYANVI JALEBI, LOCATED AT JUNA, BILASPUR - (FAMOUS FOR JALEBI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - CHINA BOWL, LOCATED AT LINK ROAD, TELIPARA - (FAMOUS FOR MANCHURIAN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - NAGPUR BIRYANI CENTER, &nbsp;LOCATED AT NEAR MAHARANA PRATAP CHOWK, VYAPAR VIHAR ROAD, BHARTIYA NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR BIRYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - SANTOSH BHUVAN, LOCATED AT GOND PARA, SADAR BAZAR - (FAMOUS FOR MASALA DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>8 - CAFFINO, LOCATED AT NEXT TO IDBI BANK, AGRASEN CHOWK, TELIPARA - (FAMOUS FOR SANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>9 - SOUTH CAFE, LOCATED AT OLD HIGH COURT ROAD, NEAR SBI BANK - (FAMOUS FOR DOSA, WADA, UTTAPAM AND IDLI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>10 - BILASPUR - {FAMOUS FOR RAKHIA BADI MADE &nbsp;WITH A FRUIT CALLED RAKHIA, CHILIES, GINGER, CORIANDER AND OTHER DRY SPICES}</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '6,9,16,19,21,23'),
(287, 14, 31, 751, 'Punjab', 'INDIA', 'BARNALA', 'sunset-997497_640.jpg', 'sunset-997497_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Barnala is one of the districts of Indian state of Punjab. Earlier Barnala was part of Sangrur district, but now Barnala is a separate district. It is a centrally located district bordered by Ludhiana district on the north, Moga district on northwest, Bathinda district on west and by Sangrur district on all other sides. It is said that Barnala was originally known as Anahatgarh. May be there was a garh or a fort in this very place long before Baba Ala Singh claimed this territory as his own. However, such relics from the past are no more. History of Barnala practically begins with the history of Ala Singh Ji. Unfortunately much of the relics from that era have also been destroyed. Therefore, visitors looking for places of historical importance in Barnala will have to go back disappointed. Yet for people who have eyes to see, Barnala has much to offer.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Barnala is visited by different categories of tourists. Some come here for business purposes. Indeed, the town not only has a number of large and medium scale industries, it is also emerging as a trading centre for the entire area. Some, on the other hand, come here to visit the historical gurudwaras as well as other religious places that dot the area. To cater to their different needs, different categories of hotels have come up in the town.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Road</strong> - The District of Barnala has a vast network of National Highways, State Highways and other Roads connecting it to all the neighbouring Districts of Punjab as well as those of neighbouring States.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train </strong>- The Railway Station of Barnala is located on Barnala Dhuri Railway route. So the direct trains for the National Capital New Delhi are available.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Air</strong> - Nearest airport is Sahnewal Airport in Ludhiana which is about 68 kms from Barnala.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - HARI OM BIKANER MISTHAN BHANDHAR KC ROAD BNL, LOCATED IN BARNALA - (FAMOUS FOR BREAD PAKODA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - BAKE N CAKE, LOCATED AT KC ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR CAKES AND PASTRIES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - RAJWARA DHABA, LOCATED IN BARNALA - (FAMOUS FOR BUTTER CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '6,35'),
(288, 14, 31, 1657, 'Chhattisgarh', 'INDIA', 'DHAMTARI', 'shiva-162780_6401.jpg', 'shiva-162780_6402.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Dhamtari is one of the oldest municipality regions with an average elevation of 317 meters in the Dhamtari district of Chhattisgarh state in India. The city is located in the fertile plains of Chhattisgarh. Dhamtari is a concise form of two terms Dhamma and Tarai. The town of Dhamtari is situated at a very scenic location with Mahanadi as its principal river. The city offers quite a few attractions to its visitors with easy accessibility to the nearby capital of Raipur. There are quite a few major dams that have been built over the years around the region which serve as tourist destinations. The Gangrel Dam here is worth a visit as it is the longest and biggest dam in the state of Chhattisgarh. The fertility of Dhamtari region is attributed to the presence of its tributaries which are the Sendur, Pairy, Sondur, Joan, Kharun and Shivnath. A host of temples make Dhamtari a semi religious pilgrimage centre with the Bilai Mata Temple being the most popular attraction among all. The domination of Paddy as the main agricultural crop here has transformed the region into a major agricultural producer. Besides this a number of products are being exported from the nearby forest areas too. One can find enormous levels of lead deposits within the region of Dhamtari. The chemical and timber industries have boomed in a big way along with rice and flour mills scattered all over the place.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Local hotels and lodges provide a comfortable stay.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airbase to Dhamtari is Raipur which is situated 16 kms from Dhamtari.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train </strong>- Trains are directly available directly to the town of Dhamtari as the place has a railway station. Trains are available regularly to other parts of India as well.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road </strong>- The city of Raipur is located at a distance of seventy six kilometres to the north of Dhamtari and regular buses will be available in this route for minimal fares. Tourists can either travel to Dhamtari directly or visit the town through Raipur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Bus </strong>- Dhamtari has its own bus station located in the heart of the city. Regular bus services from CSRTC are available to surrounding cities. Interstate services too are available that are operating to other states such as Orissa and Maharashtra.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Buses are the best way to travel in Dhamtari.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SANDEEP RESTAURANT, &nbsp;LOCATED AT SANT LAHARI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR DAAL AND PANEER PARATHA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - PUTTU VEG, LOCATED AT CHITAUD - (FAMOUS FOR PANEER BUTTER MASALA AND DAL FRY)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '6,8,19,21'),
(289, 14, 31, 751, 'Punjab', 'INDIA', 'FARIDKOT', 'sikh-658521_640.jpg', 'sikh-658521_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Faridkot city is located in Punjab the north western State of India. It is a municipal council and division with headquarter at Faridkot, located at an average elevation of 196 meters. Faridkot lies in south west of Punjab and is encircled by Ferozepur District In The North West, Moga and Ludhiana districts in the north east and Bathinda and Sangrur districts in the south. Faridkot and Kotkapura are the two development blocks in the district. Earlier to Faridkot it was named as Mokal Har by Faja Mokalsi, founder of the town. Later on the city of Faridkot derived its name from the name of Baba Fariduddin Ganjshankar, who is well known and famous as an ardent lover of God whose teachings appears in the Holy book of sikhs, Guru Granth Sahib. This great saint had halted in this city while on a trip from Hansi to Delhi. Faridkot is a famous city in the district of Faridkot in the state of Punjab. Prior to independence, the city of Faridkot was princely state and has a rich historical value. The locality is very old and it is found that it dates back to the period of Indus Valley. Many interesting visiting spots and places are located in this region. The official language of Punjab, Punjabi is spoken in the regions of Faridkot.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The city of Faridkot provides good facility of accommodation. Travellers can enjoy the stay with amenities offered by Budget and Luxury hotels with affordable prices. These hotels offer good facilities like room service, laundry, a/c rooms and Wi-Fi connectivity for the convenience of the visitors. One can also book online before hand to avoid hassles on arriving.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Raja Sansi International Airport in Amritsar is the closest and major International airport situated near Faridkot. It is located around 125 kms from the city. Airport has both domestic and international flights, which are well connected to several important cities of the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- The city of Faridkot owns a railway station which connects to different places, such as Bathinda, Ferozpur, New Delhi, Jaipur etc. Amritsar Junction is the nearest major Railway Station for the city.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Tourists can arrive here by bus from Punjab and Haryana. It is connected by road with Chandigarh, Bathinda and Firozepur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - PEPSU Road Transport Corporation manages the road transport in Punjab and other states of north. Both intercity and interstate bus services are provided by PEPSU to the city passengers of Punjab. Bus Station of Faridkot is located around 3 kms from the Krishi Vigyan Kendra.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - BHAIYA SWEETS, LOCATED AT B-VIII/296, LINE BAZAAR ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR BARFI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - SETHI MILK DAIRY AND SWEETS SHOP, LOCATED AT &nbsp;BALBIR BASTI - (FAMOUS FOR BUTTER KULFI)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(290, 14, 31, 751, 'Punjab', 'INDIA', 'FATEHGARH SAHIB', 'portrait-1588361_640.jpg', 'portrait-1588361_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Fatehgarh Sahib is a historical town in the state of Punjab. It holds an important place in the history of Punjab and is well known as the battle ground of the war between Sikhs and Muslims. Fatehgarh Sahib Tourism holds significance owing to the famous Gurudwara Fatehgarh Sahib, which is the place of the martyrdom of Sahibzada Fateh Singh and Sahibzada Zorawar Singh, sons of Guru Gobind Singh Ji. They were bricked alive by Wazir Khan, Faujdar of Sirhind, on their refusal to change their religion. Fatehgarh Sahib, meaning the Town of Victory, signifies the triumph and independence of Sikhs from the tyrannical rule of Muslims. In the year 1710, Sikhs, led by Banda Bahadur, fought a fearsome battle against Muslims and finally grounded the fort built at the time of Balban&#39;s rule. This town is bound by four gates, respectively dedicated to Deewan Todar Mal, Nawab Sher Muhammed Khan, Baba Banda Singh Bahadur and Baba Moti Ram Mehra. These gates have high architectural value and also signify the cultural diversity and secularity of the place. The climate of Fatehgarh Sahib is quite similar to most parts of north India. The city experiences hot summers, cool and humid monsoons, and cold winters. Amongst these variations, the best time for Fatehgarh Sahib Tourism is the pleasant months of October through March.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are a lot of deluxe and medium to budget accommodation options in the nearby regions. Hotel Antheia, Hotel Mount View, Hotel Landmark, City Heart Premium, Hometel Chandigarh, Hotel Aroma Complex, Hotel Shiwalik View, KLG International and Hotel Paras are deluxe accommodations near the city. Other medium to budget accommodations include Floating Hotel, Hotel Surya Palace, Hotel Shingar Regency and Heritage Hotel Chandigarh.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Roads are well connected from most of the parts of the Punjab towards Fatehgarh Sahib.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air -</strong> Chandigarh airport is the nearest airport which is around 50 kms from Fatehgarh Sahib.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- Buses services are good in most of the parts of Punjab, so tourists can reach Fatehgarh Sahib easily by buses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train -</strong> Fatehgarh Sahib has its own Railway Station so one can easily reach here from most of the parts of Fatehgarh Sahib.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SAMOSA JUNCTION, LOCATED AT OPPOSITE DISTRICT COURT, STATE HIGHWAY 8 - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSAS)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(291, 14, 31, 751, 'Punjab', 'INDIA', 'FAZILKA', 'b59.jpg', 'b60.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Fazilka is a city and a municipal council in Punjab, India. In 2011, it was made the headquarters of the newly created Fazilka district. Fazilka can be termed as a &quot;Religious Town&quot;, wherein the god fearing and spiritual citizens have created a &ldquo;Gowshala&rdquo;, which is an asylum for cows, an animal revered in the Hindu religion. The population here is a whopping 1000 cows, Fazilka Green Gowshalla is also an epitome of being eco friendly, having bio gas plants and energy efficient electrical fittings. Availability of fresh milk in its unadulterated form is another attraction. Tourists must visit Saravdharam Yoga Kendra every morning and evening for exercises and meditation retreats for better spiritual orientation and personal health. The city is located on Indo-Pak border and hence has faced many hardships during the time of partition and also during 1965 &amp; 1971 wars between India and Pakistan. Previously a Muslim dominant area, Fazilka is now a secular area with both Sikhs Hindus and Muslim residing in peace. It now has seven main Hindu temples. The area experiences an extreme climate with hot summers and cold winters. There are many tourist places attracting a number of tourists. The famous Sutaj River flows by Fazilka and then entering Pakistan. Joint Indo-Pak retreat ceremony of BSF and Pak Rangers attracts a number of tourists every evening. The town has many small scale cottage industries. It is also a famous agricultural region producing some of the fines varieties of wheat and rice. The area was also once famous for its cotton production which is now tremendously decreased. The town offers a good transportation medium for its tourists and residents.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Fazilka has a number of hotels from cheap hotels to expensive hotels. These hotels are famous for their hospitality. There are many star hotels in Fazilka and many are coming up. These hotels provide the best of luxuries to meet international standards. Even the economic hotels provide best of the facilities to their customers. Most of the hotels are ideally located near railway station and tourist spots. Some of the hotels also provide pick and drop facilities to railway station. The food and the accommodation facility provided in these hotels are also very exquisite.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - Sri Guru Ram das Ji International airport in Amritsar is the nearest airport to the city of Fazilka, at a distance of 203 kms.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train </strong>- Fazilka has its own railway station that was established in 1898. Fazilka railway station is located on Firozpur Bathinda broad gauged railway line, and is well linked with all the major railway heads of the Punjab.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road </strong>- The city of Fazilka is located on the National Highway 7 and State Highway 20. It is well linked by all the major cities of Punjab.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Bus </strong>- Fazilka is well connected with several major towns of Punjab by bus route. Punjab roadways run several bus services from all major cities of western Punjab.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - DES SAMOSA POINT, LOCATED AT BANIYA MOHALLA - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - DAULAT SWEET SHOP, LOCATED AT RAJA CINEMA ROAD, SECTOR 1, SARAFAAN BAZAAR - (FAMOUS FOR TOSHA &nbsp;IS A SWWET MADE FROM MAIDA(PLAIN FLOUR), BAKING POWDER, GHEE, SUGAR AND &nbsp;VANILLA ESSENCE)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(292, 14, 31, 751, 'Punjab', 'INDIA', 'FIROZPUR', 'sugar-cane-1112800_640.jpg', 'sugar-cane-1112800_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Located in the state of Punjab, Firozpur city is situated on the banks of the River Sutlej and is very close to the border between India and Pakistan. It is widely famous as the Land of Soldiers as the locals join the defence forces in hordes. Firozpur was founded by a Muslim ruler of Tughlaq dynasty, Sultan Firoz Shah Tughlaq. Ferozepur City Guide is incomplete without a mention of its rich heritage. The city contributed immensely in India&rsquo;s struggle for Independence. Shaheed Bhagat Singh Monument, Barki Memorial, Pothimala and several other monuments which pay homage to the freedom fighters are located in Firozpur. The city has numerous reputed institutes and organizations. The Arya Orphanage, started by Swami Dayanand, the founder of Arya Samaj in October 26, 1877 is a well known institute, which has given shelter to thousands of orphans and impoverished is spread over an area of 21 acres. Firozpur not only has a number of historical monuments, but also many religious shrines and natural attractions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>a). Abohar</strong><br />\r\nAbohar city is a Municipal Committee in the district of Fazilka, located in the north western state of India, Punjab. Abohar is spread on 804.24 sq kms of land area. It is located at an average elevation of 178 mts above sea level. Abohar city is situated in the south western region of Punjab close to north western border of India. It is surrounded by the cities Malout and Bathinda in the east, Hanumangarh in the south, Shri Ganga Nagar in the south west and Fazilka in the North West and Sri Muktsar Sahib in the north east regions respectively. The city of Abohar is called as trinity of the culture, civilization and ethnicity of Punjab, Haryana and Rajasthan as it shares borders with those three states. It is believed that, the city of Abohar was founded during 12th century by King Abheraj Bhatti and named it as &#39;Abhegarh&#39;. Later it became as Abohar. Abohar is the largest city and is popularly known as &#39;California of Punjab&#39; due to its rich soil, source of good irrigation and especially for the production of the fruit Kinnow, a fruit of Orange family.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Several luxury and budget hotel are present in Firozpur that cater to all the requirements of the visitors. To ensure that the visitors have a great stay, the hotels provide all the facilities. They are also well furnished. All the hotels offer clean and comfortable rooms, and basic facilities like car hire for travel, doctor on call, digital TV, laundry and dry cleaning, intercom in all the rooms, 24 hours room facility, in house generator, and hot and cold water among various other services.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- The closest airport to Firozpur is the Amritsar Airport, which is about 131 kms away. Travellers can hire a cab or board a bus or train to commute to the city from the airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - A convenient way to travel to this city is by train as it is connected to several major Indian cities by regular trains. The Firozpur Railway Station is situated in the Firozpur Cantonment Division that can be easily reached by taxi or cab.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Firozpur is connected to major Indian cities like Delhi, Amritsar and Chandigarh by road. It is convenient to travel to the city by car, bus or taxi as the roads are well maintained.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - State motor coaches attach the location to many of the cities in the state such as Amritsar, Delhi, Ludhiana and Chandigarh.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - MEHMAAN RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT CANTONMENT AREA - (FAMOUS FOR MUSHROOM MASALA &nbsp;AND DRY MANCHURIAN)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - KAKKE DA DHABA, LOCATED AT MALL ROAD, CANTONMENT AREA - (FAMOUS FOR LASSI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - SAMOSA JUNCTION, LOCATED AT BESIDE RAYMOND&#39;S SHOWROOM, MALWAL ROAD, MODEL TOWN - (FAMOUS FOR PANEER SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - MAHINDERPAL JALEBI SHOP, LOCATED AT DHOBI MOHALLA - (FAMOUS FOR JALEBI)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(293, 14, 31, 1657, 'Chhattisgarh', 'INDIA', 'JANJGIR- CHAMPA', 'sunset-1097625_6401.jpg', 'sunset-1097625_6402.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Created in the year 1998, on the 25th of May, the district of Janjgir-Champa can be found in the centre of Chhattisgarh, hence the popular term, The Heart of Chhattisgarh. This is one of the fast developing towns of the state, as it plays an important role in the production of food grains. Janjgir-Champa is in the city of Maharaja Jajwalya, who belonged to the Kulchury Dynasty. The locals who live in the district are the ones who have mostly migrated from neighbouring villages. The places in the district of Janjgir-Champa bear the names which are related to the castes of the locals such as Kahra para, Khale para, Bhatapara and so on. The Hasdeo Bango project undertaken in this district is said to be a great form of support to the villages, as 3/4th of are of Janjgir-Champa will be covered for irrigation. This district is an important agricultural hub and is also famous for fresh farm supplies and Lime stones. Famous for its culture with an ancient touch, Janjgir-Champa also has a rich culture that reflects the town&rsquo;s history. An interesting fact is that, this district had been a home to Annie Funk, a Christian Missionary who passed away during the Titanic Ship Disaster. Like the rest of Chhattisgarh Janjgir-Champa has a tropical climate. Summers are usually from April to June. The temperature gets hot and humid during summers and drops to a great extent during the winters.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">While enjoying tourist attractions of Janjgir-Champa, the tourists can also entertain themselves via comfortable and enjoyable accommodation provided at the various hotels of this region which provide multiple modern amenities for the relaxed stay of its guests.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The Raipur Airport is the nearest airport to Janjgir-Champa and it links to other major destinations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train </strong>- Janjgir-Champa is located on the Howrah Mumbai Main Line and is also is linked to the Rail Line of South Eastern Central Railway. Naila and Champa are the two railway stations of this district. The capital city of Raipur is at a distance of about 170 kms from the Janjgir district.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - The district of Janjgir-Champa is located at Janjgir, which can be reached by road through various means of transportation, as it is at a distance of about 65 kms away from Bilaspur and 170 kms away from Raipur.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - FANDU, LOCATED AT RANI ROAD, CHAMPA BASTI - (FAMOUS FOR ALOO-BONDA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - LALU SWEET&amp; RESTARUNT, LOCATED AT JANJGIR - (FAMOUS FOR TEA AND SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - KALKATTA RESTORENT,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT JANJGIR - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA AND CUTLATE)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(294, 14, 31, 751, 'Punjab', 'INDIA', 'KAPURTHALA', 'dahlia-1643808_640.jpg', 'dahlia-1643808_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kapurthala, also known as the City of Palaces and Gardens, serves as the administrative headquarter of the Kapurthala district. The city is named after Rana Kapur, a scion of the Rajput Gharana of Jaisalmer, who founded this place in the 11th century. With a rich history and vibrant culture, this city is sure to capture the attention of any traveller. Located in the culturally rich state of Punjab, Kapurthala is a historic city resplendent with architectural marvels and cultural heritage of the yore. It is the administrative headquarters of Kapurthala District and was the capital of the princely state in British India. The city has an affluent cultural heritage inherited from the culture and tradition of past centuries. Kapurthala Travel Guide is incomplete without a mention of its rich heritage. Jagatjit Palace, Moorish Mosque, Shiv Mandir, Panch Mandir, Gurdwara Chhevin Padshahi, Devi Talab Mandir and Shalimar Gardens are the prominent attractions of the city attracting large number of tourists round the year. Kapurthala is very popular for the production of the crops like wheat, sugar and cotton. It is a home to many medium to large scale industries. The city has become the major market for purchasing the several kinds of rice varieties such as Basmati and non Basmati rice, parboiled rice, sela rice and raw rice.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>a). Phagwara</strong><br />\r\nPhagwara is one of the major cities and commercial hubs in Kapurthala district of Punjab State. Being an emerging commercial hub, Phagwara city boosts a very sound infrastructure across all the important services. The city was in fact very recently accorded status of Municipal Corporation. Owing to its huge concentration of NRI population, Phagwara city is also popularly known as NRI city across Punjab state. The city resides on Delhi Amritsar National Highway 1 and is located between two big cities of Ludhiana. Although there is no comprehensive information available about history of Phagwara city, but few details of random historical events do exists. According to one such information, Phagwara city was founded by Mughal emperor Shah Jahan as a small market town. The city was then believed to be has been part of Ahluwalia Sikh Dynasty of Kapurthala, which was one of the indigenous Sikh kingdoms of Punjab region. Some history books also suggest that Sixth Sikh Guru Shri Guru Hargobind Sahib Ji visited Phagwara region in year 1635, after he had triumphed in battle of Kartarpur and Palahi.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">One can get accommodation of every range in Kapurthala. Right from 5 stars to 4 stars and also 3 star hotels that fit just right on the pockets. It has a good number of options for decent stay. Tourists can enjoy a comfortable stay at hotels which are equipped with all the necessary comforts to provide travellers a fine stay.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Roads are well maintained so driving is a great option if want to travel Kapurthala, tourists can hire cab or can drive through own vehicle.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest worldwide aerodrome from Kapurthala is Raja Sansi Worldwide Airport, Amritsar, approximately one and half hours propel from Kapurthala.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Bus services are really good in most of the places of Punjab, so if want to travel Kapurthala tourists can easily take private owned buses or can take state government bus services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The city has its own trains Station entitled as Kapurthala trains position. It is well attached to the major cities like Delhi, Bathinda, Jammu and Jalan.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - BASANT RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT BSNL ROAD, KAPURTHALA ROAD, NEAR DISTRICT COURT - (FAMOUS FOR MOMOS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - AHUJA SWEETS, LOCATED AT AMRITSAR ROAD, OPPOSITE TEHSIL &nbsp;- (FAMOUS FOR BARFI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - SHAM SWEETS, LOCATED AT JALANDHAR ROAD, SHANTI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSAS AND PAKORAS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - NEW KHALSA BAKERY, LOCATED AT MALL ROAD, SUKHJIT NAGAR, SHIVAJI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR CAKES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - TANDOORI FLAMES BLOCK 32, LOCATED AT BH2 BLOCK -A, KAPURTHALA - (FAMOUS FOR CHHOLLE BHATURE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - GROVER VAISHNO DHABA, LOCATED AT NEAR BUS STAND, SUKHJIT NAGAR, SHIVAJI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR PARATHAS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - OVEN EXPRESS, LOCATED AT INSIDE LOVELY PROFESSIONAL UNIVERSITY, GT ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR PASTA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>8 - KAPURTHALA - (FAMOUS FOR SHEER KHURMA IS A DESERT MADE FROM VERMICELLI, MILK, DATES, CASHEW NUTS, CARDAMOM AND BUTTER)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(295, 14, 31, 1657, 'Chhattisgarh', 'INDIA', 'KABIRDHAM', 'clouds-1840568_640.jpg', 'clouds-1840568_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kabirdham was earlier known as Kawardha district and is situated between Durg, Rajnandgaon, Raipur and Bilaspur. It stretches over an area of 4447.5 km&sup2;. Kabirdham is a serene and peaceful place which is favoured by the nature lovers. The surrounding is picturesque with forests, mountains and religious sculptures. Western and northern part of Kabirdham is bounded by Maikal mountain ranges of Satpura. It is located on the southern bank of River Sakari. It adds to the beauty of the place. Hills and forests make the spot mesmerising. Vast stretches of greenery treat the eyes. The name of the place originates from the advent of Kabir Sahib. His disciple, Dharmdas also had his seat at Kabirdham. It had remained Guru Gaddi Pith of Kabir Panth from 1806 to 1903. Kawardha was formed by Mahabali Singh in 1751. The name changed to Kabeerdham in 2003. It was a princely state under the British rule and was part of Bilaspur. Agariya is the language mostly spoken by the people residing here, especially those belonging to the region of Maikal Hills. Haf and Phok are other rivers flowing through Kabirdham. Kesmarda in Maikal range is the highest peak here. Kabirdham is one of the destinations for upcoming airstrip.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kabirdham has a lot of medium to budget accommodation options. &nbsp;Some of the comfortable hotels include Palace Kawardha, Hotel Kalpana, Godana Resorts, Hotel Jagdamba Palace and Hotel Royal Celebration. The hotels are homely and laced with the modern amenities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air -</strong> Swami Vivekananda Airport in Raipur is the nearest airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train </strong>- Raipur is the closest railway station on Mumbai Howrah main line.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Buses are readily available from Kabirdham to nearby cities. Raipur is 117 kms, Rajnandgaon is 143 kms and Jabalpur is 242 kms by road.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - MADHU SWEETS, LOCATED AT SARDAR VALLABH BHAI PATEL NAGAR, JAMNIPALI, KORBA - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA CHAAT)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - NEW KALPANA RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT NEAR BUS STAND - (FAMOUS FOR DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(296, 14, 31, 751, 'Punjab', 'INDIA', 'MALERKOTLA', 'sculling-1654368_6401.jpg', 'sculling-1654368_6402.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The city of Malerkotla is a municipal council in the district of Sangrur in Punjab. Malerkotla is located on State Highway 11 on Sangrur Ludhiana road in Punjab, and at a distance of 36 kms north from the district headquarters of Sangrur and 45 kms south from Ludhiana. It is strategically located at an average elevation of 248 mts above sea level. Malerkotla is surrounded by some of the major cities of Punjab such as Ludhiana on the north, Sangrur on the south, Patiala on south east and Barnala on west. The city of Malerkotla was divided into two parts Maler and Kotla. The town of Maler was founded by an Afghan named Sadr-u-din during 1466 AD, and probably, Maler has been named after Malher Singh, who built Malhergarh Fort here. The area of Kotla was established by Bayazid Khan to the south of Maler during 1656. Previously, it was known as Kotla Maler and later on came to be called as Malerkotla. Malerkotla is one of the biggest cities, and is the only industrial town of worth the name in the district of Sangrur. Due to its proximity with Ludhiana and Sangrur, several small industries have been established in the city. The economy of the town is mostly dependent upon agriculture and small scale industries. Malerkotla is well known for the manufacture industries of cycle parts and agricultural equipments. As it is a Muslim dominated town, it houses many mosques in and around the city. The town of Malerkotla has a great significance in the movement of freedom struggle, and especially in the Namdhari movement against the British during 1872. About 66 Namdharis were killed by the British on 17th and 18th of January 1872. Kukas were used their own schools, and Panchayat to avoid the British in their surroundings.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">a). Sangrur<br />\r\nSangrur is a beautiful city in the state of Punjab. Named after Sanghu, a Jatt, this city was founded 400 years back. It is the capital of the erstwhile Jind state and is located at a distance of 56 kms from Patiala. This city is also known as the &#39;City of Gurdwaras&#39; as there is over 20 Gurdwaras here, which contribute to the popularity of Sangrur tourism. Sangrur is a land with fertile and rich soil with abundant water supply. The recent establishment and development of the city was observed around 2300 BC. The people from the lands of Baluchistan and Sindh came to this fertile land in search of a better livelihood. They reached in this flourishing land from Sutlej, also known as Ghagger, which is located in Rohira. The soil was fertile and full of treasures of minerals which gave a boost to the farming sector. The development was noticed fast yet steady. People then started building sturdy houses out of bricks which were sun dried. The land flourished in many other trades of commerce. People arrived from various places. There was a huge market for pottery of the best quality. The houses were more spacious and built from good quality raw materials. The construction and city layout was impeccable. Sangrur was established about 400 years back by a Jatt, who was one of the Sanghu.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Malerkotla offers accommodation facilities for the tourists including economy Lodges and deluxe hotels. Visitors can choose their accommodation as per their needs and budget. For those who are looking for high end luxury accommodation, the luxury hotels are located in Ludhiana at a distance of 45 kms from Malerkotla.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Ludhiana Airport, also called Sahnewal Airport is the nearest airport to the city of Malerkotla located at a distance of 45 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Malerkotla has its own railway station on Ludhiana Sangrur broad gauged railway line. The railway line of Malerkotla is linked with all the major cities of Punjab.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Malerkotla is located on the SH 11 of Punjab, and it is connected with all the major cities of Punjab such as Ludhiana, Sangrur, Sunam, Patiala and Chandigarh. It lies on the Sangrur Ludhiana road.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Punjab roadways and PEPSU RTC runs number of bus services between Ludhiana and Sangrur. Plenty of bus services are available to reach Malerkotla from Sangrur.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - MULTANI DHABA, LOCATED AT NEAR BADMINTON CLUB, GURU TEG BAHADUR COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR PARATHAS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - PANDIT CHAT BHANDAR, LOCATED AT JAMALPURA - (FAMOUS FOR CHAAT PAPDI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(297, 14, 31, 751, 'Punjab', 'INDIA', 'MANSA', 'tamil-1355990_640.png', 'tamil-1355990_6401.png', '<p style="text-align:justify">Mansa, popularly called the area of white gold, is situated in east Punjab on the Barnala Sardulgarh Sirsa road. This place was originally a part of the Phulkia Sikh Dynasty before becoming a part of the Kaithal Sikh Kingdom. Its roots can be traced back to the Indus Valley Civilisation as the Archaeological Survey of India found remains of Harappa and Mohanjodaro in some of its villages. The city of Mansa shares its borders with the Bathinda district and the Sangrur district. The state of Haryana borders Mansa on the southern side. It is believed that Bhai Gurdas laid the foundation of this city. A fair is held every year in March April in his honour, wherein devotees offer laddus and gur on his samadhi. Festivals like Holi, Diwali, Dusshera, Baisakhi and others are also celebrated with fun and frolic. Baisakhi is generally celebrated on 13th April, wherein farmers express their gratitude towards god for an abundant harvest and pray for better yield in the future. Mansa is called the &lsquo;area of white gold&rsquo; as it lies in a highly fertile region of Punjab. Hence, agriculture is the main occupation here, with cotton being the main crop. &nbsp;Mansa tourism introduces travellers to warm and hospitable locals. The roadside dhabas are perfect for relishing authentic and traditional delicacies of Punjab. The city of Mansa experiences sub-tropical climate with hot and dusty summers. Monsoons are short with very low rainfall and high humidity levels. The post monsoon season is characterised by cool weather conditions, which make it perfect for Mansa tourism. It is followed by the winter season with low temperatures and cold winds.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">While travelling around the historical city of Mansa, the travel vacationers can certainly relax at its well modernized hotels. These hotels offer accommodation at affordable rates but with multiple modern amenities. They are located in proximity to the major tourist attractions of the city and provide easy accessibility to the guests. One can also enjoy scrumptious food items at their multi cuisine restaurants besides enjoying professional or private event at their indoor and outdoor venue. The courteous staff of Mansa hotels welcome each and every guest with great hospitality and ensure every facility would be utilized by them.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport to Mansa is the Sahnewal Airport in Ludhiana. All major domestic airlines like operate daily flights to Sahnewal Airport from different destinations across the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - Located on the Bathinda Jind Delhi railway line, Mansa is connected by frequent trains from New Delhi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Mansa is well connected by buses from all the major cities of Punjab. Many state transport bus operators offer daily services on the Barnala Sardulgarh Sirsa highway.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - YADAV SWEETS, LOCATED AT MAIN BAZAR ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR BARFI AND GAJARPAK)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - NIKKI FAST FOOD, LOCATED AT NEAR BUS STAND, GURU ARJUN DEV NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR GOL GOPPA(PANI PURI))</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(298, 14, 31, 751, 'Punjab', 'INDIA', 'MOGA', 'sunset-997497_6402.jpg', 'sunset-997497_6403.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Moga is a city and a municipality in Moga district in the Indian state of Punjab. It became part and headquarters of 17th District in the state, Moga district of Punjab State on 24th day of November 1995, by then Chief Minister Harcharan Singh Brar. Before this, Moga was a part of Faridkot District as a tehsil. Moga town is situated on the National Highway 95 Ferozpur Ludhiana road. The area of Dharamkot block with 150 villages has been merged into Moga district, which falls under the jurisdiction of Ferozpur division. Moga was founded by Moga Singh Gill a forefather of the Gill community. Then this city went to the hands of his two son khushpreet Singh Gill and Jagdeep Singh Gill. This divided the whole city into two parts. Till now Moga City is divided into those two parts. Moga is a newly formed district of Punjab with a prominent historical background. The district itself is the proud land of Lala Lajpat Rai&rsquo;s birth. Dhudhike Falls the native village of Lalaji is a part of Moga district. It was a sub division of Faridkot for a long time. Comprising of an area of 2209 sq km, Moga is surrounded by Sangrur district in the South, Jalandhar in north, Ferozpur and Faridkot in west and Ludhiana in the east.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">There are many hotels and guest houses in Moga. Along with 3 star hotels there are budget hotels too. These are good budget apartment stays which also provides you luxuries equivalent to hotels. There is a good range of choices for travellers who are looking for budget or holiday bargain.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest airport is located at Amritsar and this is located round 108 kms from the location.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Train </strong>- The town of Moga is attached to Amritsar, Jaipur and a couple of other locations by train.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Road</strong> - Roads are well maintained, tourists can easily hire a cab or can easily drive through own vehicle.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Government buses attach the location to most of the nearby towns and villages and this is furthermore a viable choice.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(299, 14, 31, 751, 'Punjab', 'INDIA', 'MUKTSAR', 'sukhna-lake-724004_6402.jpg', 'sukhna-lake-724004_6403.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Muktsar is a municipal council and administrative district head quarters of Muktsar district, located in the north western state of India, Punjab. Muktsar is also known as Sri Muktsar Sahib. Muktsar is situated in south western region of Punjab and is encircled by Bhatinda in the east, Ferozepur in the west, Faridkot in the north and Rajasthan and Haryana in the south. The area of Muktsar comprises of 5.19% of Punjab, which is about 2615 square kilometers. Muktsar derived its name from 40 Martyrs, Muktas disciples of tenth Sikh guru, Guru Gobind Singh Ji who fought a war against Mughal Army in 1705. Muktsar literally means &lsquo;Mukat or Mukti&rsquo; that is Salvation and &lsquo;Sar&rsquo; is Sarovar, thus a pool of liberation. Muktsar is a significant historical and pilgrim city, closely associated with Sikh religion. On 7th November, 1995 Muktsar was formed as a separate region by withdrawing its subdivision from the district of Faridkot, which was earlier the subdivision of Ferozepur District. Punjabi and Malwai dialect is the local language spoken in Muktsar like most of the other cities of Punjab. Agriculture is the basic and vital activity and the major source of income for the people of Muktsar.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The city of Muktsar provides basic accommodation facilities for the travellers. There are a handful of stupendous hotels, resorts and lodges that offer a cosy, tranquil and outstanding accommodation to the tourists visiting the city. All the hotels in Muktsar have well furnished AC as well as non-AC rooms with all the latest amenities at very affordable price ranges.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - Muktsar has no aerodrome, Amritsar aerodrome, Raja Sansi International Airport is the nearest and major International aerodrome to Muktsar. It is established about 175 kms from the town. Airport has both household and international air travel, which are well connected to several significant towns of the homeland.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - Muktsar has a trains junctions, situated on Mallgudam Road, the rail path between Kotkapura and Fazilka in Muktsar city. It is established about 1.5 kms from centre of the town. Muktsar railway position belongs to to the north Railways and connected by very wide measure lines.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - The city of Muktsar is well connected by the road ways to all the major towns and cities of Punjab and other states of north India.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Bus</strong> - Muktsar has a Bus Stand, located about &frac12; km from the city and 2 kms from Muktsar railway station. Both public (Punjab roadways and Pepsu Road Transport Corporation, PRTC) and private buses are available at short intervals to reach inter-city and inter-state regions.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - ROYAL FOOD,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT 414, KOTKAPURA RD, BHULLAR COLONY, GURU ANGAD DEV NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR CHANNA MASALA AND GOL GAPPE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - PAPPU, LOCATED AT NEAR MUKTSAR CLUB, KOTKAPURA ROAD, DEEP NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n', '');
