(300, 14, 31, 1657, 'Chhattisgarh', 'INDIA', 'MUNGELI', 'sunset-1367138_640.jpg', 'sunset-1367138_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Mungeli is a municipality town and District Headquarter of Mungeli District, which was bifurcated from Raipur district just couple of years back and was made into a separate district. In that sense Mungeli is a very new town. Although this young town is nowhere as developed as its counterpart cities like Raipur and Bilaspur, but is blessed with lot of scenic beauty. However, its scenic beauty has still not been harnessed to tap tourism potential of this town. Mungeli is a fast developing census town located in Bilaspur district of Chhattisgarh state. Mungeli is a small but picturesque city loaded with scenic beauty and panoramic views to enchant its visitors. It is a census town but not as urban as the nearby Bilaspur or the capital city of Raipur. The city still enjoys a traditional culture which can&#39;t be labelled as a cosmopolitan. The people are warm over here and help visitors to explore the place in their own traditional way. The city may not be attractive at first sight but its charming aura will slowly but surely start gripping the tourists. The place exudes oodles of traditional charisma which attracts not only a multitude of nature lovers but also the adventurous throughout the year.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Mungeli, although a small place, offers various accommodation options to choose from. It houses budget hotels and guest houses to luxury and premium hotels.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air </strong>- Bilaspur Airport which is 48 kms at Chakarbhatta is the nearest airport to Mungeli but no scheduled airlines offer their services currently. Officially, the nearest airport is Raipur Airport aka Mana Airport which is 95 kms, which has regular flights for all major cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail </strong>- Mungeli is near to Bilaspur railway station, which is a regional hub for the Central Railways.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Bus</strong> - Narayanpur Bus Stand which is 34 kms from Mungeli is the nearest bus stop to reach the city. Regular services are available from CSRTC.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Mungeli can be reached easily through Bilaspur, which is well connected with Mumbai and Kolkata via Raipur through National Highway 200 connecting Raipur and Raigarh on either side. Regular CSRTC bus services and taxis ply on a regular basis to all surrounding towns and cities.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(301, 14, 31, 1655, 'Jammu & Kashmir', 'INDIA', 'PULWAMA', 'mountains-1622731_6401.jpg', 'mountains-1622731_6402.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Mist clocked snow capped mountains, tall trees with iced dewdrops, greenery as far as the eyes can see and colourful display of flora, perfectly describes Pulwama in Jammu and Kashmir. Popularly known for its milk and rice production it&rsquo;s also called the&rdquo; Rice Bowl of Kashmir&rdquo;. From temples to waterfalls to lake, a trip to Pulwama ensures of diverse attractions to choose the tourist destinations. Soak up the breathtaking fresh beauty of Tarsar and Mansar lakes, fall prey to natures wonder at the Aharbal Falls, and feed the adventurous soul at Shikargah, an attraction for its wildlife. The Mughal Road with its historical significance attracts a lot of tourist Pulwama is dotted with many religious sites. Payer Temple, carved out of a single stone as believed by the people, Avantishwar temple, a sacred place, and many shrines attract many people from around the globe. The peace and quiet atmosphere along with fresh air is sure to revitalize and energize the visitor. The district comprises of 323 villages, which are grouped in 5 tehsils namely, Awantipora, Shopian, Pulwama, Tral and Pampore. Situated at a distance of about 40 km from Srinagar, Pulwama got the status of the district in 1979. Pulwama was earlier known by the name of Panwangam that was later renamed to Pulgam. The district of Pulwama was ruled by the Kashmir Sultanate from 1346 to 1586 AD. The Mughal rulers came here in the 16th century, and during the early 19th century, the Afghans began to rule the region.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are several hotels, lodges and home stay facilities available in Pulwama.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Tourists can reach there by road one can easily hire cab or can get buses from Srinagar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Airways</strong> - Nearest airport is Srinagar airport, if wish to come by air then must have to hire cab or have to take bus from Srinagar airport to Pulwama.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Bus</strong> - Bus will be the convenient mode as one can get buses from Srinagar the average distance is around 340 kms from Jammu to Pulwama.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - Nearest railway station is Jammu Tawi railway station, station is well connected to all other major stations in India.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - PULWAMA - {FAMOUS FOR MATSCHGAND IS A A DISH OF MINCED MEATBALLS WHICH IS COOKED IN SPICY RED GRAVY}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - FOOD GALLERY, LOCATED AT NEWA - (FAMOUS FOR BIRYANI AND KEBABS)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(302, 14, 31, 1658, 'Odisha', 'INDIA', 'PURI', 'water-768745_640.jpg', 'water-768745_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">One of the four must visit pilgrimage sites for Hindus; Puri is a beach city with its most famous attraction as the Jagannath temple. Known as the resting place of Lord Shiva, Puri in the state of Orissa is situated alongside the coast of Bay of Bengal. This town is home to one of the most sacred temples in Hindu mythology, the Jagannath Temple. The majestic history and heritage of Puri dates back to the 3rd century BC. Puri, Konark and Bhubaneshwar complete the Golden Triangle of Orissa, with their religious significance and cultural heritage being the centres of tourism in this state. Puri is soon turning into an industrial hub with major manufacturing companies coming here. The Rath Yatra which takes place during the month of June-July should not be missed planning to visit during this time. Located in the state of Orissa, Puri is one of the holiest pilgrimages for the Hindus. Puri is a coastal city that stands on the banks of Bay of Bengal. Featuring great architectural building, balanced climate, exotic beaches, beautiful landscapes and historical significance, Puri is visited by tourists all year round. Puri also holds great historical significance because it is believed to be the land of Lord Jagannatha.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">With the Rath Yatra taking place in the month of July, it can be quite difficult to find accommodation. In any case, it is best to book book rooms in advance here. The hotels offer packages that cater to all types of visitors from honeymooners to students. The hotels near the temple tend to overcharge. Remember to check in to a room with an air conditioner during the summer. Puri has its share of beach side hotels that offer a great view of the Golden Beach and don&rsquo;t necessarily burn a hole in tourist&rsquo;s pocket.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest airport is Bhubaneswar. Puri is just an hour journey from Bhubaneswar which is around 56 km away. The Bhubaneswar Airport is well-connected to others parts of Odisha as well as India. Buses are taxis are available from the airport to Puri.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail</strong> - There is a railway station in Puri. Direct rail services are available from Puri to many important places in Odisha as well as India such as, Kolkata, New Delhi, Guwahati, Bangalore, Chennai etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road -</strong> Puri is connected by well maintained road. State own buses as well as private buses are available from all the major places in Odisha. Puri is connected with the neighbouring cities through well constructed roads. Buses are considered to be the main option to travel to Puri as the bus stand in near the Gundicha Temple. Bhubaneshwar and Cuttack can be reached in 15 minutes by bus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Tranport </strong>- Delux buses from Orissa Tourism Development Corporation (OTDC) can be availed for sightseeing and other tourist activities in Puri. Travelling within the city is facilitated by various modes of transport like cycle-rickshaw, auto-rickshaw and hired motorbikes. Cycle rickshaws are the most economical option. The meters of the auto rickshaws usually don&#39;t work so one must know how to strike a bargain.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - PURI - {FAMOUS FOR CHHENCHEDA IS A NON-VEGETARIAN DISH MADE FROM &nbsp;FISH HEADS LIKE ROHU, BHAKURA OR MIRIKALI AND VEGETABLES LIKE EGGPLANT, POTATOES, TOMATOES, RIDGE GOURD, ONIONS AND SPICES ; ALU POTALA RASA IS A TYPE OF CURRY MADE FROM POTALA (GOURD), ALU (POTATOES), GINGER, GARLIC, ONIONS, COCONUT, CUMIN, CHILLI AND TURMERIC POWDER ; &nbsp;KHAJA IS A SWEET MADE FROM WHEAT FLOUR, SUGAR, OIL}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - NEW PARIJAT RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT SEA BEACH - (FAMOUS FOR CHILLI CHICKEN)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - DALMA, LOCATED AT VIP ROAD, NEAR FIRE STATION - {FAMOUS FOR CHINGUDI TARKARI( SMALL SHRIMP CURRY), KUKUDA MANSA KASSA TARKARI (CHICKEN WITH POTATOES)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - TANDOORI BITES, LOCATED IN PURI - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;TANDOOR CHICKEN)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(303, 14, 31, 1657, 'Chhattisgarh', 'INDIA', 'RAIGARH', 'actor-1807558_640.jpg', 'actor-1807558_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">A city and municipality in Raigarh District in Chhattisgarh state of India, Raigarh was the capital of the princely state of Raigarh. A city with a rich cultural heritage, Raigarh lies on the eastern border of Chhattisgarh, and is famous for its verdant forests, cascading waterfall, beautiful parks and temples. Embark on a Tour to Raigarh to visit and explore this enchanting city of Chhattisgarh. One of the specialties of Raigarh is Dhokra Casting the art of producing metal ware by the process of hot wax casting. The tribals of Raigarh are adept at this art. Raigarh is also famous for its silk products including the Tassar Silk and Mulberry Silk. Besides, the city is a well known centre for Kathak dance and classical music. A good time to plan a Tour to Raigarh is during the &#39;Chakradhar Samaroh&#39; festival held on Ganesh Chaturthi every year. This festival witnesses music and dance exponents from all over India visiting Raigarh and displaying their art. The major tourist places worth visit while on Tour to Raigarh in Chhattisgarh include the Ram Jharna a natural water source which is also a popular picnic spot. The Gomarda Forest Reserve, which houses several species of rare and endangered wild animals including tigers is also a must visit place on your Raigarh Tour.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Raigarh offers few budget hotels complete with arrangements for food.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- There are no regular flights from other major cities of the country to Raigarh. Nearest airport is Raipur Airport. There is also a private airport located 10 kms northwest of the city owned by the Jindal Steel and Power Limited.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail </strong>- Raigarh is well connected to other major cities of the country via regular trains. The Raigarh station is located on the Tatanagar Bilaspur section of Howrah Nagpur Mumbai line. It comes under the Bilaspur railway division. It is well connected with many major cities</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - One can easily get regular buses to Raigarh from other major cities of the country. Raigarh is well connected via roadways to other parts of the state and country.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Auto-Ricksaws, hand pulled rickshaws and Taxis form a major part of local transportation network in the city of Raigarh. Tourists can book taxi to reach other parts of the city or for travelling to other parts of the district.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - RAIGARH - {FAMOUS FOR MUTHIA IS A SNACK MADE FROM RICE BATTER WITH VARIOUS SPICES ; CHILA IS A SNACK PREPARED FROM RICE BATTER MIXED WITH &nbsp;URAD DAAL}</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(304, 14, 31, 738, 'gujarat', 'INDIA', 'RAJKOT', 'lamp-2490_640.jpg', 'lamp-2490_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Rajkot is a city of Gujarat state in India and administrative headquarters of the Rajkot District, located on the banks of the Aji River and Niari River. Rajkot is famous as the capital of the former state of Saurashtra. Rajkot, though no more a capital, has always had a glorious past and still is a favourite tourist spot due to the historic remains from the British era and also the hospitality of the Rajkot people. Rajkot was founded in 1620 AD by Thakore Sahib Vibhoji Ajoji Jadeja, a descendent of the Jamnagar Royal Family. Rajkot was named after the co-founder Raju Sandhi. Thakore Sahib was awarded territories for helping the Mughal Emperor to regain his footings in Gujarat. Along with that he also confronted the local Kathi tribes and the ruler of Junagadh to strengthen his state. The tourism in the city is picking up owing to the fact that there are a number of places here that are worth visiting. One reason for Rajkot&rsquo;s fame can be attributed to India&rsquo;s greatest freedom fighter, Mahatma Gandhi, who spent his early years here and also married his wife in this town. Pre-independence, Rajkot was under various rulers. After India&rsquo;s independence, it was separated from Bombay and became a part of the newly-formed state of Gujarat on 1st May, 1960.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The small city has various hotels, motels and lodges which are sure to fit all kinds of budgets. Rajkot provides its visitors a whole range of options to choose from. From luxury star hotels to economic accommodation with facilities apt for a comfort stay to guest houses with just basic facilities. Please discuss needs and requirements and negotiate the charges before finally reserving the accommodation.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Located just a few kilometres away from the main city, Rajkot Airport is a domestic airport connected to the main cities in India and Gujarat.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail </strong>- Rajkot Junction connects the city to all corners of India. Various express and passenger trains are available to all destinations within and outside the state. All major cities are well connected with Rajkot.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Rajkot is connected to the rest of the state through the Gujarat State Highways and Gujarat State Road Transport Corporation operated buses, plying within Rajkot and other cities of Gujarat. Also there are private buses connecting the city to the other cities within the state and other states.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Rajkot Municipal Corporation operates CNG fuelled buses within the city. Taxi services, auto rickshaws and private cabs are also available.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - RASIKBHAI CHEVDAWALA, LOCATED AT JUBILEE ROAD, LIMDA CHOWK, OPPOSITE PANCHNATH MANDIR, LIMDA CHOWK - (FAMOUS FOR CHEVDO, PETISH)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - JAYSIYARAM PENDAWALA, LOCATED AT KALAWAD ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR PEDA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - SANKALP RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT RACE COURSE CHOWK - (FAMOUS FOR SOUTH INDIAN FOOD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - MAYUR BHAJIYA, LOCATED AT GONDAL ROAD AND KOTECHA CHOWK&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;- (FAMOUS FOR BHAJIA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - TADKA EXPRESS, LOCATED AT JAMNAGAR - RAJKOT HIGHWAY, OPPOSITE B.A.DANGAR HOMEOPATHY COLLEGE - (FAMOUS FOR DAL BATI, CHURMA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - QWICHES, LOCATED AT KKV HALL,KALAVAD ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR SANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - TOMATO&#39;S, LOCATED AT SHITVAN - B, KALAVAD RD, ROYAL PARK - (FAMOUS FOR PAV BHAJI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>8 - SACHA SODA PUNJABI DHABA, LOCATED AT SHIVAJI PARK, NH 8B, NAVAGAM - (FAMOUS FOR DAL MAKHANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>9 - BALAJI, LOCATED AT SANGANVA CHOWK, SIR LAKHAJIRAJ ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR CHEESE SANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>10 - KUTCHI KING, LOCATED AT GURUPRASAD MAIN ROAD, KRISHNA NAGAR, SARDAR NAGAR - {FAMOUS FOR DABELI IS A SNACK MADE FROM POTATOES, MASALA, PAV (BURGER BUN)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>11 - RAJ PAUBHAJI, LOCATED AT AJANTA COMPLEX, GONDAL RD, OPP BOMBAY HOTEL, VIJAY PLOT, BHAKTI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR PAV BHAJI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>12 - AASHAPURA PENDAWALA, LOCATED AT ASHAPURA MAIN ROAD, VAISHALI NAGAR, PRAHLAD PLOT - {FAMOUS FOR KESAR PENDA AND THABDI (CARAMELIZED SWEET MADE FROM MILK)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>13 - SHREE RADHESHYAM SWEET &amp; FARSAN, LOCATED AT 2, POLE STAR COMPLEX, KALAVAD RD, JAGANNATH CHOWK, NEAR GIRIRAJ HOSPITAL, JAGANNATH PLOT - (FAMOUS FOR FARSAN IS A SNACK MADE FROM &nbsp;POTATOES, GRAM FLOUR)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>14 - JAGAD SWEET MART, LOCATED AT SONI BAZAR, KATRIWAD, SONI BAZAR - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORI AND SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>15 - SHREE AKHILESH CHIKI, LOCATED AT SHOP NO. 3, GROUND FLOOR, UNIQUE SHOPPING CENTRE, ASTRON CHOWK, SARDARNAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR CHIKI AND JUICE)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(305, 14, 31, 1657, 'Chhattisgarh', 'INDIA', 'RAJNANDGAON', 'stairs-338428_640.jpg', 'stairs-338428_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Rajnandgaon was carved from Durg district on January 26th 1973. Shanskardhani is another name of Rajnandgaon which focuses the peace and harmony that thrives amongst people of various religion of this place. It is bounded by ponds and rivers and is famed for some small scale industries and trades. Durg and Bastar border Rajnandgaon in the east and south respectively. It is 73 kms from Raipur and an airstrip is being planned here in the recent future. Originally named as Nandgram, Rajnandgaon was ruled by various dynasties in the ancient days. Somvanshis, Kalchuris and Marathas are some of them. Palaces in this region reveal more about the rulers and the then society during their reign. Culture and tradition of this period is reflected through these palaces. Rulers were mostly Hindus like Vaishnav and Gond Rajas. It has also remained the capital of Raj Nandgaon princely state during the British rule. The last ruler of the princely state gave his palace for the opening of college which was named after him. Hindi and Chhattisgarhi are the languages spoken by the inhabitants of this region. Rajnandgaon houses many educational institutes. Diwali and Ganesh Chaturthi are the main festivals of this place which are celebrated with lots of zest and enthusiasm. &quot;Mohara Mela&quot;, &quot;Bull Run&quot; and Mina Bazaar are organized during these celebrations.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Rajnandgaon has propelled as a tourist attraction in recent years. The presence of the pilgrimages and the ancient architectural excellence has also showcased the potential of the city as a tourist place. The demand and necessity of good and budget hotels have phenomenally increased in the city due to a large influx of tourists in the city.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Raipur airport is 87 kms from Rajnandgaon and is the nearest one to this place.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail</strong> - Rajnandgaon lies on Mumbai Howrah line of South Eastern Railways. Local trains for Donrgargarh, Nagpur and Raipur are available from here while express trains connect Kolkata, Mumbai and Delhi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- National Highway 6, Great Eastern Road passes through Rajnandgaon which connects it to various cities. The city has two major bus stands. The old bus stand and the new bus stand have frequent services which connect to the nearby cities. State capital Raipur is connected by the bus service.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - PUNKH RESTAURANT (PURE VEG), LOCATED AT OPPOSITE HDFC BANK, NEAR RAILWAY STATION, TANKA PARA - (FAMOUS FOR PANEER CHILLY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - ABIS CHICKEN DELIGHT, LOCATED AT BUDDHA SAGAR, LAKE VIEW ROAD, NAGPUR - BHANDARA - RAJNANDGAON - RAIPUR HWY, KAILASH NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN TIKKA &nbsp;AND CHICKEN CHILLY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - M M CHAT CORNER, LOCATED AT NATIONAL HIGHWAY 6 - (FAMOUS FOR SANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - MANAV MANDIR, LOCATED AT SH 5, JAI STAMBH CHOWK - (FAMOUS FOR POHA, KACHORI AND SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - SHAN-E-PUNJAB FAMILY RESTAURANT AND DHABA, LOCATED AT NH 6, NEAR 8TH BATTALION BARGAH - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN TIKKA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - DESHMUKH RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT SH 5, CHIKHALI - (FAMOUS FOR POHA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - JALARAM SNACKS AND NAMKEEN, LOCATED AT NEHRU NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR DHOKLA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n8 - MAHENDRA CHAT CORNER &amp; FAST FOOD, LOCATED AT AZAD CHOWK, WARD NO. 32 - (FAMOUS FOR PANI PURI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>9 - MOTI SWEETS, LOCATED AT HALWAI LINE - (FAMOUS FOR RASGULLA)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(306, 14, 31, 1655, 'Jammu & Kashmir', 'INDIA', 'RAJOURI', 'mountains-1800870_640.jpg', 'mountains-1800870_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Rajouri a scenic district located in Jammu and Kashmir is flanked by Poonch in the north, Naushera and Chhamb in the south and the Line of Control in the west. Comprising of six boroughs; the mesmerizing landscapes of Rajouri are largely mountainous and fertile. The lush rice and maize fields in the region are nurtured by the waters of River Tawi, which in turn are fed by the snowy peaks of Pir Panjal. Tourists visiting Rajouri are inspired by its rich treasure trove of languages, festivals, cuisines and cultures. Along with Urdu and English as the main languages, Dogri, Gujri and Pahari are the other regional dialects spoken in the area. The much acclaimed Bakarwal and Gujjar tribes are reputed for herding goats, horses and sheep and are known to speak Gujri. Here, the local populace is divided on the lines of religious faiths and live together in perfect harmony and peace. Rajouri District is one of the popular tourist destinations in Jammu &amp; Kashmir. This destination was initially a part of the Poonch District. In 1968, Rajouri was declared an independent district. The Jaral Dynasty ruled the district of Rajouri from 1194 to 1846 AD. Forts and mosques located in Rajouri were constructed during the rule of the Jaral Dynasty and thus represent architectural style of that era.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The issue with hotels in Rajouri, since quite a while remains that the pricing of the rooms is as per 4 star hotels, but the hotels themselves are no more that 2 to 3 stars. It&#39;s imperative to exercise caution while choosing accommodation here and have booking stone before hand, with proper research, than to shuffle around the city with luggage in the middle of the trip.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Rajouri is well connected to all nearby foremost places within the state Jammu &amp; Kashmir or neighbouring states by Road network.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Airways </strong>- Rajouri Airport is just 15 kms away from the city center.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Direct bus between Jammu and Rajouri is available, best is to take State Transport Bus from Jammu to Rajouri.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - No direct trains are available between Jammu to Rajouri. Shri Mata Vaishno Devi Katra Railway Station is the closest railway station which is about 65 kms from Rajouri.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - ASHIRWAD, LOCATED IN RAJOURI - (FAMOUS FOR CHIKEN CURRY)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(307, 14, 31, 1655, 'Jammu & Kashmir', 'INDIA', 'REASI', 'rocky-mountains-1082208_640.jpg', 'rocky-mountains-1082208_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Reasi is a small place in the district with the same name in the state Jammu and Kashmir. In 8th century the place was under the Sikh ruler Raja Gulab Singh. The place experiencing a cool summer and chilling winter is blessed with a wide variety of sightseeing places loved by people belonging to all age groups. Every Indian who believes in god will have longing desire to visit the Vaishno Devi Shrine popularly known as &ldquo;Vaishno Devi Yatra&rdquo; atleast once in his/her lifetime. Katra in Reasi is the base point to start a 12 kms long walk to touch the feet of the Vaishno devi Mata perched in the snow fed caps of the mighty Shivaliks and feels blessed. The seat of governance of the Gujri and holding the distinction of being one of Jammu and Kashmir&rsquo;s oldest towns, Reasi was founded by Raja Bhim Dev in the 8th century. Until 1822, Reasi had remained as an independent principality and was then taken over by Raja Gulab Singh, the Governor of the hill region of Jammu. After a lot of administrative changes in the status of Reasi, it is now an integral part of District Poonch.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Neelam Hotel is the best hotel in the town. The hotel offers all the latest amenities to the tourists and it has gained a lot of popularity in this area. Thus, one can bank on this hotel once hit the town of Reasi.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Nearest Airport is Jammu Airport which is just 44 kms away from the Reasi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail</strong> - Shri Mata Vaishno Devi Katra Railway Station is just 15 kms away from the Reasi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Tourists can easily hire cabs or buses from Jammu; it is somewhat 45 kms from Jammu city. Bus service is too much frequent to Katra from Jammu, Himachal as well as Delhi, one can easily hire buses.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - PREM VAISHNO DHABA, LOCATED AT MAIN BAZAR, KATRA VAISHNO DEVI, REASI, KATRA - (FAMOUS FOR NAAN AND KULCHA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - REASI - {FAMOUS FOR ROGAN JOSH IS A CURRY MADE FROM &nbsp;LAMB, ALKANET ROOT ; MODUR PULAAV (SWEET PULAO, IS A DESSERT MADE FROM SUGAR, GHEE, BAY LEAVES (TEJ PATTA), CINNAMON, CARDAMOM, BLACK PEPPER, DATES, ALMONDS, CASHEW NUTS AND RAISINS}</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(308, 14, 31, 739, 'Haryana', 'INDIA', 'REWARI', 'www.jpg', 'www1.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Rewari is a town in the Rewari district in Haryana. Located about 89 kms from Delhi, it is part of the National Capital Region. History has it that Hemu, the last Hindu emperor of India, was brought up and educated in Rewari. His haveli still stands in the Qutabpur area of the city. During his time, the emperor had laid the foundation of a metalwork industry in copper sheets, utensils, and brass manufacture. It is still famous for these products. Rewari was a part of the Gurgaon district in Haryana. It later became a part of Mahendergarh and remained so till 1989, when it became an independent district. The main attraction of Rewari is the Rewari Heritage Steam Locomotive Museum. The shed housing the museum was built in 1893 and is the only one in India hosting a few steam engines that have survived the wear and tear of their strenuous journeys. Rewari has a dry, semi arid climate. It experiences three distinct seasons: summer, winters and monsoon.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Apart from giving a great eating experience, tourists stay is also well looked after. From three to one starred hotels, one will find it all in Rewari based on the budget. Heritage hotels are also a part of this city which is not just a great place to stay, but one to experience as well.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Road </strong>- It is well connected by road which connects all other major cities and states by NH 8, NH 71, NH 71B.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport is Indira Gandhi International Airport, Delhi about 83 kms from Rewari.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Bus</strong> - HSTC and private buses services are frequently available to ply Rewari from all other major states and cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - Rewari has its own railway station which connects to all other major cities and states.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - DAWAT, LOCATED AT NEW COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR ALOO CHAT)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - TADKA, LOCATED AT GARHI BOLNI ROAD, MODEL TOWN - (FAMOUS FOR SPRING ROLLS AND MOMOS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - HARI SINGH SWEETS, LOCATED AT OPPOSITE MAIN POST OFFICE, CIRCULAR ROAD, SH 26 - (FAMOUS FOR LASSI (BUTTERMILK) AND SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - GOLE HATTI, LOCATED AT CIRCULAR ROAD, NAI BASTI - (FAMOUS FOR CHOLE BHATURE AND JUICES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - APSARA CAFE, LOCATED AT MODEL TOWN - (FAMOUS FOR KULFI LACCHA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - BABA BHARTI DHABA, LOCATED AT DODHAI - (FAMOUS FOR PARATHAS AND FALUDA RABRI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n7 - SHREE JEE SWEETS, LOCATED AT MODEL TOWN - (FAMOUS FOR PEDA AND RASMALAI)&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(309, 14, 31, 739, 'Haryana', 'INDIA', 'ROHTAK', 'lily-1239860_640.jpg', 'lily-1239860_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Rohtak is a district in the Indian state of Haryana, with a town by the same name as its capital. It is situated near Delhi and comes under National Capital Region II. It is about 70 kms from Delhi and is also the political capital of Haryana. Rohtak is also famous for its dairies, cloth market and educational institutes. It is believed that Rohtak traces its roots to the times of Indus valley civilization. The Minars that have been excavated at Khokhrakot are typical of the Indus valley times. It also finds mention in Mahabharata as Rohitika. Rohtak was also possibly the capital of Bahudhanyaka the kingdom of Yaudheyas. The coin moulds of the Yadhyayas of the 3-4 century AD have been discovered in a large number. The fact that the town existed during the Kushanas is testified by the Khushana Pillar Capital found here. The pillar is decorated with carving of winged lions and riders. It is believed that Rohtak continued to flourish till the 10th century AD. Today, Rohtak is home to several educational institutes. It is also famous for the Indian snack, Rewri. The climate of Rohtak is varied in nature.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are many resorts and hotels in Rohtak that cater to all sections of people in Rohtak. The rooms with the hotels are all very commendable and offer the traveller great accommodation facilities while visiting Rohtak. Almost all have standard, deluxe and super deluxe rooms which cater to all kinds of people and their varied budgets.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Rohtak has road network is excellent which connect all the major cities and states.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport to Rohtak is Indira Gandhi International Airport which is about 75 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Bus</strong> - HSTC, private buses and all state corporation buses are ply frequently between all the major cities and states.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - Rohtak has its own railway station which is connected to all the major cities and states.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - NATHU&#39;S SWEETS, LOCATED AT NH 10, MODEL TOWN - (FAMOUS FOR PANI PURI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - NEW LIGHT SWEETS, LOCATED AT QUILLA ROAD, SALARA MOHALLA, BABRA MOHALLA - (FAMOUS FOR RASOGULLA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - TAPASYA PARATHA JUNCTION, LOCATED AT DELHI BYE PASS, BUS STAND WALA ROAD, RAJIV CHOWK - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;AALOO PARANTHAS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - CHAHAT RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT OPP. SERVICE CLUB, CIVIL ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR PANEER ADRAKI DHANIYA WITH LACHHA PRANTHA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - PANDIT CHAT BHANDAR, LOCATED AT NH 10, SUBHASH NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR DOSA, BHALLE PAPRI, AALOO TIKKI AND KULFI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - M3 COFFEE CAFE, LOCATED AT SAT GURU KRIPAN COMPLEX, NEAR PUNJAB NATIONAL BANK, DELHI ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR BURGER AND PIZZA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - NAGPAL, LOCATED AT PURANI SABZI MANDI ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR CHOLE BATURE)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n8 - A - ONE SWEETS AND NAMKEEN, LOCATED AT BABRA MOHALLA - (FAMOUS FOR GULAB JAMUN AND SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>9 - POONAM SWEETS DOUBLE PHATAK, LOCATED AT CHAWLA COLONY, JANTA COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA AND BREAD PAKORA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>10 - SHANKAR SWEET CORNER, LOCATED AT SALARA MOHALLA, PAHARA MOHALLA - (FAMOUS FOR KALAKAND)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>11 - GINNI RASGULLE WALA&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;, LOCATED AT SUNARIAN ROAD, ROHTAK STATION DIARY MOHALLA - (FAMOUS FOR RASGULLA, BARFI, GULAB JAMUN)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(310, 14, 31, 1658, 'Odisha', 'INDIA', 'ROURKELA', 'swan-1114270_6401.jpg', 'swan-1114270_6402.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Rourkela stands as a majestic city nestled in natural surroundings, endowed with hills and enriched by rivers. The splendid city is a part of the tribal hub, the Sundargarh district. Situated at a distance of 325 kms from the capital city of Bhubaneswar, Rourkela is a fine example of the harmonious existence of tribal culture amidst modern day settlement. Known as the commercial capital of Odisha Rourkela offers a wonderful opportunity to witness natural beauty in an industrial township. The place is famous for its various natural and man-made attractions. This city came into focus for having the Rourkela Steel Plant, which introduced CCTV to the continent of Asia for the first time in 1984. The largest steel city of Odisha, Rourkela is a steel city; however its natural positioning makes it an offbeat tourist location for people of nearby areas. Conveniently located in the lap of nature, Rourkela is one of the first cities of the country to become commercialized for steel production. Rich in naturally occurring minerals, Rourkela has also been blessed with a variety of relief features and natural tourist destinations that attract tourists. Falling in the Sundergarh district, it is considered best to head to Rourkela in order to visit the other popular destinations in the district.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Apart from budget inns and luxury hotels, there is a government run guest house for accommodation. Odisha tourism recommends several hotels and lodges to stay in Rourkela. Some of them are Hotel Apsara, Hotel Mayfair, Hotel Radhika and Rourkela House. Hotels here offer the simple gesture of genuine hospitality and high standard of services.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\n<strong>By Air</strong> - Rourkela Airport connects the city to several other towns and cities of India. A number of flights by DTDS create the link between Rourkela and the other places in India. There are regular flights to Jamshedpur, Bokaro, Patna, Ranchi, Bhubaneswar and Kolkata.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail</strong> - Rourkela Railway Station is the link between the commercial city and the rest of the country through the rail network. There are regular trains that carry passengers to and from Rourkela. The rail network is an easy way to reach the city of Rourkela from various parts of the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Rourkela has a strong network of highways and national highways that connect it with several parts of Odisha and the country. Regular buses run between Rourkela and some other towns and cities of Odisha. Taxis and private vehicles are also available for hire to reach the nearby places from Rourkela.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- The three-wheeler auto taxis are the most important mode of transportation in the city. Taxis also ply on the city&#39;s roads. Sampark City Service buses, introduced in September 2006, connect various areas in the city. To commute within the city autos and buses are the two most popular medium, the autos are cheap and easily available.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - ROURKELA - {FAMOUS FOR PAKHALA IS A DISH MADE FROM RICE, CURD, CUCUMBER, CUMIN SEEDS, FRIED ONIONS AND MINT LEAVES AND SERVED WITH ROASTED VEGETABLES(POTATO, BRINJAL) AND SAGA BHAJA OR FRIED FISH ; KANKADA JHOLA (CRAB CURRY) MADE FROM POTATOES, ONION, GINGER, POWDER OF (CARDAMOM, CINNAMON, TURMERIC AND RED CHILLY) AND CRAB}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 -NEELAM RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT BANK STREET, SECTOR 19 - (FAMOUS FOR CHOLE BHATURE AND MANCHURIAN)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - GANGAUR, &nbsp;LOCATED AT CIVIL TWP - (FAMOUS FOR DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - SHAHI DAWAT, LOCATED AT SECTOR 2 - (FAMOUS FOR BIRIYANI, PANEER ROLL, CHICKEN ROLL, CHICKEN CURRY AND LACHA PARATHA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - LAZEEZ RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT S13, NAC MARKET, KOEL NAGAR A BLOCK - (FAMOUS FOR ROLLS, KABABS, CHICKEN BIRYANI AND MOMOS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - ISPAT FOOD COURT, LOCATED AT SECTOR 5 - (FAMOUS FOR GOLGAPPA, EGG CHICKEN ROLL, VEG MANCHURIAN, DABELI AND PAV BHAJI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - LUCKY FOOD PLAZA, LOCATED AT NEAR VSS MARKET, CHHEND COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR MANCHURIAN)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n8 - KAILASH PURI, LOCATED AT KACHERY ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR KAJU BARFI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(311, 14, 31, 733, 'Assam', 'INDIA', 'BAKSA', 'bird-1038316_640.jpg', 'bird-1038316_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Baksa district was carved out of a part of Nalbari, Barpeta, Kamrup and a small portion of Darrang district. As a result of the historic BTC (Bodoland Territorial Council) accord signed on February 10, 2003, BTAD (Bodoland Territorial Autonomous Districts) was formed with four districts namely Kokrajhar, Chirang, Baksa and Udalguri. Baksa district has an area of 2400 sq kms and the district headquarters is Mushalpur. As the original word &#39;Baksa&#39; has been derived from various sources and antecedents, there exists a lot of controversy over the name and a good chunk of population prefer to use &#39;Bagsa&#39; in lieu of &#39;Baksa&#39;. Though there are many popular sources and folklores about the origin of the name, no historical source has been found till date. Peoples say that the name &quot;Bagsa&quot; is originated from Bhutanese language. According to Bhutanese origin they denoted the area as &quot;Bagsa Duar&quot; Bagsa means one kind of rice and Duar means entrance point. Bhutanese king ruled these areas for a long time in an around first half of the 19th century, so it might be possible that the name &quot;Bagsa&quot; or &quot;Baksa&quot; had a Bhutanese origin. According to Bodo source the name originated from a kind of rice grain which is known as &quot;Bagsa&quot;. The said rice grain is one kind of broken and unclean product which is gained after milling the rice.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">A wide range of resorts, hotels, Government run lodges and guesthouses to suit every budget offer memorable stays here at Baksa among welcoming local people and stunning natural surrounds.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Nearest Airport to Baksa is Gopinath Bordoloi International Airport at Borjhar in Guwahati.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The nearest railway station is Tihu which fall under Nalbari district at a distance of 35 kms from District HQ. The distance of Nalbari Railway Station from Dist. HQ is about 45 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Nearest Bus stand to Baksa is Guwahati Bus Stand.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>BAKSA - (FAMOUS FOR POSOLA IS A FOOD MADE FROM THE INNER PART OF BANANA SHOOTS)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(312, 14, 31, 733, 'Assam', 'INDIA', 'BARPETA', 'sunset-343864_640.jpg', 'sunset-343864_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Located in the state of Assam, Barpeta is an administrative district, whose headquarters is based at the town called Barpeta. Covering an area of 3245 sq kms, Barpeta comprises of mainly two sub divisions, namely Barpeta and Bajali. The district shares its border with Bongaigaon district in the west and Nalbari district in the east. In south, the district is bounded by Kamrup and Goalpara district, while in the north it is surrounded by Bhutan Hills. Barpeta is a town that is located in the Barpeta district of the state of Assam. The town is a popular tourist destination and one can see many people from various parts of the country through the year in this place. The place has always had religious importance and contains many historical and religious places. Many sataras are located in the town of Barpeta and these are good places to visit while, travelling to the region. Some of the main sataras are Moinbari Satara, Barpeta Satara, Kanara, Baradi, Sundaridia, Jania, Patbaushi and Ganakuchi. The place also has a rich cultural heritage and many forms of dance can be seen in the place. One can also see different forms of traditional and ethnic arts during the festival season. During the Doul festival one can witness the Holi Geet, which is a form of chorus singing. The place is also famous for its arts and crafts; there are many centres that are located in and around the town that make traditional carvings out of wood. One can also find ivory carving centres in the town. These can be purchased as souvenirs. Tourists can also find many traditional paintings in the town of Barpeta. Best time to visit Barpeta is during the months of October and November.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The accommodation options at Barpeta Satra offer a variety to choose from, for different kind of travellers. Barpeta Satra has their own guest house and dormitories for pilgrims. With the approval of the administrative office tourists can stay there. Satra accommodation is free of cost. Apart from that there are hotels available in Barpeta at very low cost. They have budget hotels, mid budget hotels. The tariff ranges between Rs. 200 to Rs. 900.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Flight</strong> - If travelling by air, the nearest airport to Barpeta is the Guwahati Airport, which is at a distance of about 98 kms from Barpeta. Taxi service is available from the airport to Barpeta.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - There are regular bus services available between Barpeta and Guwahati. Small cab services are also available from Adabari of Guwahati to Barpeta town.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - If travelling by train, tourists will have to get down at Guwahati station from where the train route is connected through Barpeta Road which is about 18 kms from Barpeta Town. Local train service is available in between Guwahati and Barpeta, morning and evening.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Rickshaws are, by far, the best modes of intercity transport, which are easily available and that too at very low rates. Tourists can get auto as well as cycle rickshaws within the cities, from which they can choose one depending upon the distance to be covered as well as the budget in hand. There are taxi services available as well.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SWAD SAGAR DHABA, LOCATED AT NATIONAL HIGHWAY 31, NEAR MANAS NATIONAL PARK, BARPETA DISTRICT, HOWLY - (FAMOUS FOR PORK DISHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - WALDEN DHABA, LOCATED AT MUSLIMPATTY, BARPETA TOWN - (FAMOUS FOR CHOWMEIN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - RESTURANT MADHUMITA, LOCATED AT BARPETA TOWN - (FAMOUS FOR PARATHA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - JEEVAN SAHA, LOCATED AT KALAHABHANGA - (FAMOUS FOR SAMAOSA AND PARATHA)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '');
