(327, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'LAKHIMPUR', 'sunset-1139296_640.jpg', 'sunset-1139296_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Covering an area of 2277 sq kms, Lakhimpur district is bounded on the north by Siang and Papumpare district of Arunachal Pradesh and on the east by Dhemaji district and Subansiri River. Majuli sub division of Jorhat district stands on the southern side and Gohpur sub division of Sonitpur district is on the west. The district headquarters are located at North Lakhimpur. The name Lakhimpur is believed to have originated from the word &ldquo;Lakshmi&rdquo;, the goddess of prosperity. Mainly agrarian, the principal crop is paddy. Paddy is regarded locally as &ldquo;Lakhimi&rdquo; and the word &ldquo;pur&rdquo; means &ldquo;full&rdquo;. Lakhimpur therefore means full of paddy or the place where paddy is grown abundantly. The soil of the district is alluvial and fertile in which crops flourish without use of any artificial manure or hard labour. The Baro Bhuyans, originally from the western provinces of India, were driven out by the Sutiya, and these in their turn gave place to their more powerful brethren, the Ahoms in the 13th century. The Burmese, who had ruined the native kingdoms, at the end of the 18th century, were in 1826 expelled by the British under the Treaty of Yandaboo. They placed the southern part of the state, together with Sivasagar under the rule of Raja Purandhar Singh; but it was not till 1838 that the whole was taken under direct British administration.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Lakhimpur is a small place which has only a few numbers of hotels and restaurants. Nevertheless they are always ready to serve the people with the finest delicacies of Assam and northeast. The hotels here have proper amenities to serve its guests.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air</strong> - The airport located in Lakhimpur is known as Lilabari airport. Located at a distance of 8 kms from the city, the Lilabari airport also serves the state of Arunachal Pradesh. Lilabari airport is connected to Guwahati and Kolkata by an Alliance Air flight on Sundays and Fridays.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Train</strong> - The railway station is situated in Nakari, just 2 kilometres from the town. There is the Arunachal Express which runs between Lakhimpur and Guwahati.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Road </strong>- For road transport one can avail the facilities of State Transport vehicles which are available to and from Lakhimpur on a daily basis. Buses are available from Guwahati, Dibrugarh, Tezpur, Tinisukia, Jorhat and Sivasagar to Lakhimpur on a daily basis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Water</strong> - Ferry services are available which connect Lakhimpur to Jorhat, Dibrugarh and Sivasagar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Cars and cabs facilities are also available for travelling in Lakhimpur. One can book any types of cabs that vary from economical, AC, Non AC and luxury.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(328, 14, 31, 733, 'Assam', 'INDIA', 'MORIGAON', 'assam-336755_640.jpg', 'assam-336755_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Morigaon or Marigaon or Mariagaon is a place packed with many surprise elements for tourists to explore. Enriched with strong history, fascinating legends and unique traditions and culture, the town is like a box of surprises, waiting to be opened. The River Brahmaputra marks the northern limits of the district and west offers the sight of snow capped Himalayas with sun peaking from its behind. The place is also an agricultural land where vegetables, jute, mustard, wheat and paddy are mainly grown and provide steady source of income for the locals. Dotted with many attractions and enriched with flora and fauna, Morigaon is also known as Marigaon and is an enchanting land of beauty and glory. Morigaon district is an extremely picturesque district covering an area of 1450.02 sq kms. Crisscrossed with numerous rivers, waterways, beels and marshes, the greater part of the region is an alluvial plain. On a clear winter day, the snow covered peaks of the outer Himalayan range can be clearly seen. Morigaon became a fully fledged district on 29th September 1989, when it was split from Nagaon district.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Marigaon offers few accommodation options which mainly include budget hotels and mid range hotels. These accommodations provide all the basic facilities along with magnificent views of nature. Tourists can also spice up the taste buds with the authentic Assamese cuisine here.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Flight</strong> - Guwahati Airport serves as the nearest airport to Marigaon located nearly 70 kms away. One can hire a taxi from outside the airport till the required destination.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road </strong>- Marigaon is a connected to its neighbouring cities and other cities of state via a well maintained network of roads. State owned as well as private buses runs regularly within the city. It is located about 70 kms from Guwahati and 40 kms from Nagaon.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train </strong>- The nearest railway station to Marigaon is Jagi Road Railway Station. It serves as the main railhead for whole district and is located on the Guwahati Lumding railway Line. Take taxi or bus from outside the station till the town.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Marigaon, in form of public transport offers bus service but it travelling the town for sightseeing and adventure better opt for the taxi for commuting from one spot to another. However, try and visit the place during winters and avoid especially the monsoon season.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - CHILLI&#39;S FAMILY RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT KK HANDIQUE PATH - (FAMOUS FOR MUGLAI PARATHA AND SOUP)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - MONI, LOCATED AT NIZ DANDUA-MORIGAON ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR CHAT ITEMS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - JUNBELI DHABA, LOCATED AT NEAR AMBA SERVICE PETROL PUMP, JAGIROAD - (FAMOUS FOR BUTTER NAAN AND PANEER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - JAIN HOTEL, LOCATED AT NATIONAL HIGHWAY 37, JAGIROAD - (FAMOUS FOR CHHOLE BHATURE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(329, 14, 31, 733, 'Assam', 'INDIA', 'NAGAON', 'india-1034837_640.jpg', 'india-1034837_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Nagaon, previously known as Nowgong, is a city and a municipal board in Nagaon district in the Indian state of Assam, situated 120 kms east of Guwahati. The Kolong River, a tributary of the Brahmaputra River, flows through Nagaon. Nagaon houses the Kaziranga National Park, which is known all over the world for successful conservation of the Great One Horned Rhinoceros. Tourist attractions such as Bordowa, the birth place of a great artsist Mahapurush Srimanta Sankardeva, Pokhi Tirtha and the Lowkhowa Wild Life Sanctuary are located in the proximity of Nagaon. Raha, a prominent trade centre of Assam is also located in Nagaon. The Jugijan Temple, Nagaon Kala Mandir and Shiva Temple, the Binapani Natya Mandir and the Puranidugam Durga Temple are major religious centres of Nagaon. Nagaon is the most populous district of Assam and one of the largest in area. It is known as the RICE BOWL of Assam. Economy of the Nagaon district is purely agrarian with paddy being the principal crop. It provides livelihood to almost 78 percent of the total population. Besides agriculture, another major livelihood earner is the fisheries. The Agar perfume industry at Hojai is world famous.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Nagaon, two hours away by road from Guwahati, has several accommodation options to suit every budget. Nagaon also has a Curcuit House and a Government run Tourist Lodge. The Department of Tourism and Assam Tourism Development Corporation Limited operate lodges and resorts at various urban, rural and wildlife destinations.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air</strong> - Nearest airport is Mumbai, approximately 118 kms from Nagaon via road.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Train</strong> - The nearest railway station to reach Nagaon Beach is Pen or Panvel. From Mumbai or Thane one can reach Panvel station by local trains through Harbour line.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Road</strong> - There are regular State Transport MSRTC bus services available, connecting Mumbai, Kolhapur and Pune to Alibaug. From Alibaug, one can hire an auto to reach Nagaon.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Water </strong>- There are regular ferry services to Nagaon from Pen and Mumbai respectively.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(330, 14, 31, 733, 'Assam', 'INDIA', 'NALBARI', 'india-1309206_6402.jpg', 'sss.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Nalbari, an administrative district, is located in the state of Assam. Nalbari covers an area of 999.9 sq kms. Nalbari is surrounded by the Indo Bhutan International Boundary on the north. Darrang and Kamrup District lie on the east, Barpeta District on the west and Brahmaputra on the south. Situated on the foothills of the eastern Himalayas, Nalbari provides opportunity for exploring the natural beauty of the region. Travellers can enjoy folk dance and music such as Bhaora, Nagra Naam, Ojapali and Theya Naam. Raax is the main festival celebrated in Nalbari during the month of November. The festival is followed by a fair and theatre performance. Billeshwar Temple of Nalbari, also known as Hari Mandir is one of the famous religious centres in the region, which is dedicated to Lord Krishna. The 500 years old shrine features a beautiful figurine of Lord Krishna. Raax festival is celebrated in this temple with great enthusiasm. Another temple of significant religious importance is the Buddhist temple, which is located on the outskirts of the town at a distance of 20 kms. The Buddhist religious centre also hosts an annual festival during which several devotees visit the shrine for paying homage. Situated in the vicinity to Guwahati at a distance of 60 kms, the town is connected with various parts of the country. This entire district is in the plains of the Brahmaputra Valley. The tributaries of the Brahmaputra, Nona, Buradia, Pagaldia, Borolia and Tihu which originate from the foothills of the Himalayan Range, contribute enormously towards the agrarian economy of the district.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Nalbari is place where tourists will find from budget hotels to mid range accommodations that provide with all the basic facilities. The stay at the hotel is comfortable and the food served is quite good.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Flight</strong> - Lokpriya Gopinath Bordoloi International Airport of Guwahati serves as the nearest airport to Nalbari. Connected to many major cities of India via regular flights, the airport lays nearly 1 hour drive from the town.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - To travel Nalbari, tourists have to first travel till Guwahati that is easily connected via state owned buses as well as private buses from the neighbouring cities. Once reached the city, taxi is the best option and the most preferred option till Nalbari which located about 60 kms away from Guwahati.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train </strong>- Nalbari houses a railway station that is very well connected to Paltan Bazaar Railway Station of Guwahati. One can avail almost any train from Guwahati till the required destination.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Nalbari like many other cities of Assam has provision of good taxi service for intra city commuting. An auto rickshaw ride can also be considered for short distance travelling. Apart from that make sure to plan the visit to the destination carefully keeping weather conditions in mind.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - NILANTRAN, LOCATED AT SANTIPUR - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN LUGHLAI PARATHA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - BARUAH FAST FOOD, LOCATED AT BARUAH ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR POKORA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - ADITYA SWEETS, LOCATED AT PROFESSORS COLONY, PALASHANI - (FAMOUS FOR SALOSAS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - KUHELIKA RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT VIP ROAD, CHRISTIANPATTY - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;ALOO PARATHA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - GREEN CHILLY RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT PRATAB SHARMA ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN FRIED RICE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - RESTAURANT NALPONG, LOCATED AT POLYTECHNIC TINIALI, BISHNU RABHA PATH - (FAMOUS FOR BUTTER CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - CHAUPAL RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT KAZIRANGA, SECONI T.E. NO. 4, ASSAM TRUNK ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR DOSA AND UTHAPPAL)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(331, 14, 31, 1653, 'Uttarakhand', 'INDIA', 'RUDRA PRAYAG', 'india-1309206_640.jpg', 'india-1309206_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Lying at the confluence of River Alaknanda and River Mandakini, Rudraprayag is a sacred place regarded as one of the Panch Prayags and place of great religious significance. Settled in Uttarakhand, this beautiful town is full of mysterious charm and the spiritual vibes that will calm you senses. Offering spectacular views and mesmerizing panoramic vistas, the town boasts of being blessed by Mother Nature in its full glory. The town derives its name from the Hindu deity Lord Shiva who is said to have appeared at the place in the form of Lord Rudra. Rudraprayag is sprinkled with several ancient temples and serves as a gateway to two major pilgrimages of Kedarnath and Badrinath, offering its visitors a surrounding of serenity and tranquillity. Tourists also get enchanted by its natural dazzling beauty and spellbinding landscapes. Tourists and devotees flock this place in large number seeking spirituality as well as nature&#39;s splendours.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Rudraprayag offers many options to its visitors when it comes to the accommodation. The place houses several mid range and budget hotels offering the best of all the services as well as the delicious food. The view from almost all the hotels is worth watching.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air</strong> - The Jolly Grant Airport of Dehradun is the nearest air base located at a distance of 183 kms from the Rudraprayag town.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Rail</strong> - The Rishikesh Railway Station is the nearest railhead to Rudraprayag. It is a small railway station with few trains.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Road</strong> - Tourists can also reach Rudraprayag by buses. This place is strategically located on the National Highway 58, which connects Delhi to Badrinath. During summers, all buses travelling from Delhi to Badrinath pass through Rudraprayag on the way to Joshimath. Regular buses are also available from Rishikesh to Rudraprayag.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Rudraprayag is a small town where one will be hiking or trekking most of the time. Other than that one can also hire taxis, or even better book a private car for comfortable commutation from one place to another. However, make sure to plan the trip timing according to the weather conditions prevailing in the area. Avoid travelling during extreme winters or peak monsoon season.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(332, 14, 31, 751, 'Punjab', 'INDIA', 'RUPNAGAR', 'hibiscus-1760931_640.jpg', 'hibiscus-1760931_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Rupnagar, formerly known as Ropar, is an ancient city situated on the left bank of the River Sutlej. This city is named after Prince Rup Sen, son of Raja Rokeshar, who ruled this region during the 11th century. It was also one of the major cities of the Indus Valley Civilization. Excavations by the Archaeological Survey of India (ASI) revealed remains from over six different periods of this civilization. To preserve and protect all these artefacts, the Archaeological Survey of India built a special museum here, which is a part of several Rupnagar tourism itineraries. The district of Rupnagar in the Patiala administrative division of Punjab lies in close proximity to Chandigarh. The district is spread over an area of 2056 sq kms formerly known as Ropar it shares boundaries with Nawanshahar, Mohali and Fatehgarh Sahib districts of Punjab. Rupnagar district was carved out on 1st November 1966 during the re-organisation of the state. Earthen wares, figurines and coins found in the region date back to the Harrappa and Mohen-Jo-Daro civilisation. Besides, the historic remains dating back to Chandra Gupta, Kushan, Hoon and Mughal period have also been found in the region. Rupnagar has also witnessed the war of Guru Gobind Singh against the Mughals. The district of Rupnagar has a dry climate with hot summers and very cold winters. Among the four seasons, the best time to visit Rupnagar is during autumn.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are luxury hotels, 3 star hotels, 2 star hotels and even cheap accommodation available in the city of Rupnagar. Tourists can easily access to the hotel of their choice according to the budget. Booking in advance is preferable to avoid hassles on arriving.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest international airport to Rupnagar in the state of Punjab is in Amritsar, around 200 kms away and can be reached in less than 4 hours by road.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - A number of trains connect Rupnagar Railway Station to cities in Punjab and other Indian states. It is directly connected to New Delhi and Himachal Pradesh by Janshatabdi and Himachal Express, respectively.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Buses, public and private, are the best mode of transportation to travel to Rupnagar from nearby cities. Tourists can also choose to travel to the city by taxi or cab.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - ROYAL SWEETS, LOCATED AT 66, STREET NUMBER 4, MALHOTRA COLONY, DASHMESH NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSE CHOLE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - LUXMI SWEETS, LOCATED AT MALHOTRA COLONY, DASHMESH NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(333, 14, 31, 1659, 'Manipur', 'INDIA', 'SENAPATI', 'tribe-718953_6401.jpg', 'tribe-718953_6402.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Senapati is one of the nine districts an in the state of Manipur and one of best destinations to visit for nature lovers. It is also name of the town which serves as the district headquarter. Like most other places in the North East this district and the town have preserved natural beauty at its best. Visitors are treated with a glimpse of the hilly landscapes, serpentine streams, pristine rivers, deep gorges and rugged mountains during their visit to this place in Manipur. If looking for some adventure during the visit to Manipur, this district is meant to offer the best. Senapati has been blessed with diverse flora and fauna which is a delight to experience. There are many places in and around the town of Senapati and elsewhere in the district for the tourists to visit and these include Maram Khullen, Yangkhullen, Mao, Liyai, Makhel,Purul, Kaubru Mountain and Houdu Koide Biisho among others.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Although currently there is nothing much to see, visitors can enjoy a relaxed holiday amidst the scenic beauty around. There is not so much variety of accommodations except for some of the lodges and government guest houses. It is suggested to plan the stay in Imphal which is about 62 kms away. &nbsp;Imphal is the state capital and an extremely well developed city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest Airport to Senapati is Tulihal Airport, Imphal which is about 65 kms away. The Imphal Airport has flight services to all major destinations of the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Rail</strong> - Senapati has no railway line. The nearest railway station is Dimapur in Nagaland which is 150 kms from Senapati. There is a narrow guage rail line from Jiribam, a small town in Manipur 275 kms from Senapati.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Road</strong> - Senapati is connected by good roads to Imphal which is in turn connected with Guwahati through National Highway No 39 and Silchar through National Highway No 53. Senapati has a bus stop that has bus services from all nearby cities. There are direct buses from Imphal very frequently.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(334, 14, 31, 741, 'Jharkhand', 'INDIA', 'BOKARO', 'india-995576_640.jpg', 'india-995576_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Bokaro is a district belonging to the state of Jharkhand which was formed in the year 1991. With an altitude of 210 mts from the seas level, Bokaro is located on the Chhotanagpur Plateau. The city is mainly comprised of valleys and streams. Bokaro can be called as one of the highly industrialized zones in India. It is a famous tourist destination and travellers visit the place all round the year. The surroundings of the city have their own picturesque beauty. The temperature of Bokaro is moderate and pleasant which makes people feel more relaxed while travelling to this place. Bokaro is a city with lakes, greenery and beautiful parks which make it a place suited for relaxation and peace. Besides being the centre of India&#39;s industrial revolution back in the 1960s and 1970s, Bokaro has been able to establish itself as one of the most well planned cities in the country. The city located on the banks of River Damodar is the largest producer of steel and iron in the country and houses some of the biggest factories. Being surrounded by a very green area it is also full of wonderful lakes and parks that dot its beautiful landscape. The city is high on culture and is truly cosmopolitan in nature.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Bokaro is a major commercial and industrial city which offers great accommodation options to visitors. One can easily get affordable accommodation here at any time of the year. Bokaro is a cosmopolitan city with many hotels and accommodations suited to the budget of any kind of traveller. Hotels here offer perfect services to make the stay more comfortable. Tourists can also book the hotels in advance to experience the best services offered by them. As per the need and demand, tourists can select the hotels which suits pocket.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport to the city is at Ranchi which is 118 kms or it takes nearly two hours to reach Bokaro from Ranchi airport. Bokaro Steel city has a private airport strip that is used only by the private carriers of SAIL and other dignitaries.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Railway</strong> - Bokaro Steel city is well connected with all the major cities and towns in the country by rail. The main station of the city is situated 12 kms from the City Centre and comes under the administration of South Eastern Railway zone of the Indian Railways.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>By Bus</strong> - The Steel city has two main private bus terminals other than the Government bus terminals. There is another private bus terminal at Chas which is just 8 minutes away from Bokaro. Naya More is the main bus terminal in Bokaro city that handles around 500 buses at a time. The bus stand is divided into platforms for private buses. There is also a government bus terminal that is situated adjacent to the main Bus Terminal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - National Highway 32 and National Highway 23 are the two major highways, on whose intersection the city of Bokaro is located.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Private cars and taxi facilities are available everywhere in the city. Regular commuting in the city is supported by numerous local transports like trekkers, autos, rickshaws and mini buses.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n1 - BOKARO STEEL CITY - (FAMOUS FOR LITTI CHOKHA, MACHER JHOL(FISH CURRY) SADHNA AND MARUA ROTI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - SHAAN-E-PUNJAB, CITY CENTRE SECTOR 4A - (FAMOUS FOR PUNJABI CUISINE)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - HIGH HUNGURY, JA14 CITY CENTRE - (FAMOUS FOR MUTTON BRIYANI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - KOZY SWEETS, LOCATED IN SECTOR 4 - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;SNACKS ITEM LIKE SAMOOSA, KACHURI, JALEBI AND LASSI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n5 - GINGER RESTURANT, CITY GCENTRE, B-18, SECTOR 4 - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN MASSALA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n6 - RAINBOW RESTURANT,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;B23 AND B25, CITY CENTRE SECTOR 4 - (FAMOUS FOR VEGETARIAN FOOD)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n7 - SRI HARI HOTEL, CITY CENTRE SECTOR 4 - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORI AND SABAJI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n8 - NATKHAT SWEETS, IN SECTOR 4 - (FAMOUS FOR LADDU, SOUTH INDIAN MASALA DOSA, UTTAPAM AND OTHER SNACKS ITEMS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n9 - KATHI JUNCTION, CITY CENTRE SECTOR 4 BESIDE ROYAL PUBLIC SCHOOL INDRA GHANDHI MARG - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;KHATTI ROLLS KEBABS, SHAWARMAS AND TIKKAS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n10 - GOLI VADA PAV, PLOT NO.22 NEAR SHREELEATHERS SHOWROOM CITY CENTRE SECTOR 4 - (FAMOUS FOR PANEER ROLL, CHEESE UNGLI, &nbsp;MAKAI PALAK VADA PAV)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(335, 14, 31, 741, 'Jharkhand', 'INDIA', 'CHATRA', 'beach-1331413_640.jpg', 'beach-1331413_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\nChatra district is one of the twenty four districts of Jharkhand state, and Chatra is the administrative headquarters of this district. The district covers an area of 3706 sq kms. The territory covered by the present district was earlier known as Chatra sub division of Hazaribagh district. This district came into existence in 1991. Chatra district is one of the districts of Jharkhand state. Chatra is the administrative headquarters of this district. Chatra district is surrounded by Bihar state from North, Palamu District from West, Latehar District and Ranchi District from south, Hazaribag district from east. Chatra is otherwise known as the gateway of Jharkhand. It is the district headquarters of the Chatra district in Jharkhand. This is a place away from the buzz of the city, providing ample scope for photography through the jungles and other scenic locations like waterfalls and fountains. Chatra is a place full of scenic views of waterfalls and forests. The place is abundant in medicinal plants and other wood like teak, bamboo, timber, etc. Tourists can also find a lot of wildlife species in the forests of Chatra. Chatra has a glorious history. The natives here are mostly tribes who would make feel at home once in Chatra. The languages widely spoken in this area are Magahi, Nagpuri and Khortha. The place ideally has a tropical wet and dry climate throughout the year. The best time to visit the place is during the winter.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Finding a comfortable stay is not a problem in the city as it has some wonderful hotels where relaxed stay is provided to the guests. The hotels in Chatra offer sojourn to the travellers within their elegant rooms, which are fully soaked with multiple modern amenities. Not just the relaxed stay, the properties also have modern dining places where tourists can savour mouth watering food items of local and international cuisines. Moreover, the hotels also benefit with their location as one can easily reach to the city&rsquo;s tourist attractions while staying at their premises.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air </strong>- Gaya International Airport in Bihar which is located 74 kms approximately is the nearest airport to reach Chatra city. The nearest airport to Chatra is in Ranchi which is about 150 kms from the place.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train </strong>- Chatra has its nearest railway station in Gaya which is about 90 kms away from the place. Trains are available to Gaya from cities in India like Delhi, Ahmedabad, Chennai, Howrah and Mumbai.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road </strong>- Chatra city is located at the crossing of NH 99 and NH 100. Chatra has a lot of good roads making it easy for road travel. In fact, buses are also available from all the major destinations located near Chatra.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - CHATRA - (FAMOUS FOR BATHU KI KHER, MAL PUA, KACHALU KA SALAN, MASH DAAL, CHANA MADRA, GHANDYALI KA KATTA, BABRU)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(336, 14, 31, 741, 'Jharkhand', 'INDIA', 'DUMKA', 'tree-fungus-1731532_640.jpg', 'tree-fungus-1731532_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Dumka is famed as the land of tribes. It is one of the oldest districts and also the head quarter of Santhal Pargana divison in Jharkhand. It was made the headquarters of the Santhal Pargana region which was carved out of Bhagalpur and Suri districts after The Great Santal Hul 1855. Presently, it is Sub capital of Jharkhand state and the commissionaires headquarter of Santal Pargana division which has 6 districts. The city is all through filled up with mesmerising beauty. Gigantic mountains, splendid landscapes, serene rivers and stretches of greenery in the valleys are a treat to the eyes. One of the twenty four districts of Jharkhand it was once amongst most backward districts of India. Dumka was originally an administrative district formed by the Britishers which was known as &#39;Damin-e-ko&#39;. The Mughals assigned this name to this and nearby areas on account of presence of hillocks and undulating terrain. Productivity of land is very less because of heavy erosion and low retaining capacity.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\nThere are some good and economic hotels in Dumka. The price range for these hotels varies from 200 to 500 rupees per day. The hotels here provide all the basic amenities for an economic price and are value for money. The hotels provide pride room facility, AC, TV, telephone etc. some hotels are located in the heart of the city and some near the tourists location. So according to choice, tourists can choose where to stay. In short, hotels in Dumka provide good stay to all the tourists of the town.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air </strong>- There is currently no airport in Dumka. The nearest airport is in the capital city of Ranchi, at a distance of about 311 kms or it takes nearly 5 hours to drive down from Ranchi to Dumka.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail</strong> - There is no railway station in Dumka, the nearest railway station to reach Dumka is Jasidih. This station is located at a distance of approximately 73.6 kms of driving distance from Dumka, and is well connected to it by road.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road </strong>- As such, Dumka is well connected to most of the major cities of Jharkhand by well maintained roads. The city is close to NH 60 and is connected by State Highway 7. Ranchi and Jamshedpur are situated at a distance of around 300 and 200 kilometers respectively. Many government, private and luxury buses ply on these roads both during daytime and night.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - MACHAN FAMILY RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT AIRPORT ROAD, LAKIKUNDI - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;MOMOS AND CHILLY CORN)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(337, 14, 31, 741, 'Jharkhand', 'INDIA', 'GIRIDIH', 'sathodi-falls-453419_640.jpg', 'sathodi-falls-453419_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Giridih is one of the famous mining towns of Jharkhand. Located at the centre of North Chota Nagpur Division, Giridih shares its border with Nawada district of Bihar in North, Deoghar and Jamtara districts in the East, Hazaribagh and Koderma in the West and Dhanbad and Bokaro in the South. It is old and beautiful hamlet located amidst the hills which has attracted tourists from the neighbouring states. In 1972, Giridih district was newly formed which was earlier a part of Hazaribagh district. Spreading over 4853.56 sq kms Giridih is a storehouse of ruby mica and coal field. The word &ldquo;Giridih&rdquo; means land of hills and hillocks which focuses the upland area of the region. Vast stretch of forests covers maximum part of the district. Sal tree is mostly found here apart from bamboo, Semal, Mahua and Palash. Giridih has a rich source of minerals Mica being one of them. Parasnath Hills or Sri Sammeta Shikharji is the most important tourist spot of Giridih. It is pilgrimage centre for Jain people. Barakar and Sakri are two important rivers flowing through the district. Usri Falls is another captivating tourist spot. Situated at a distance of 13 kms the river here is seen falling from 40 ft steep height.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The city of Giridh has been equipped with plenty of hotels of various quality and affordable prices. Here are some hotels where tourists can find the place while touring Giridih. Many hotels offer special packages during festive season when Jain tourists from far and wide visit the popular Parasnath hills.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Though there is no airport in Giridih, a landing airstrip fulfils some of the necessities. Boro aerodrome is located at the head quarter of Giridih. Nearest airport is Birsa Munda Airport in Ranchi at a distance of 208 kms from Giridh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Single passenger train runs from Madhupur Junction to Giridih Station five times a day. They are distanced by 54 kms and are connected by single broad gauge railway line. Parasnath Station is another important station which is 48 kms away from Giridih.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Giridih is well connected by roadways as Grand Trunk Road passes through the district. Giridih is situated at the junction of NH 2 and NH 100.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Bus terminal being located in the centre of the city is easily accessible from any corner. Both private and Government buses are available. Regular bus service not only connects every corner of the district but also connects Dhanbad, Bokaro, Ranchi, Jamshedpur, Hazaribagh and Deoghar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Local means of transportation include trekkers, autos, rickshaws, mini buses and private taxis.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center">GIRIDIH&nbsp;- - [FAMOUS FOR LITTI AALOO CHOKHA, MITHA KHAJA, DHUSKA,( DUBHNI, CHILKA &amp; ARSA ROTI), BEDMI PORI, RUGRA, THEUKA, HANDIA, BAMBOO SHOOTS, KANDA, PUA, DHUSKA, GHUNGI]&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(338, 14, 31, 741, 'Jharkhand', 'INDIA', 'PALAMU', 'girl-1209908_640.jpg', 'girl-1209908_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Palamu is one of the districts of Jharkhand state and renowned for its Tiger reserves. Palamu, located in Palamu district, is bounded by Son and Bihar rivers on the north, Chatra and Hazaribagh districts on the east, and by Latehar District and Garhwa district on the south and west, respectively. The fertile land of Palamu and its rich wildlife attracts a large number of tourists. Daltongunj is the headquarters of the district. The region has a wide variety of flora and fauna and also holds historical significance. The scenic beauty of the place is a visual retreat for the tourists. River Koel along with its tributaries Auranga and Amanat flows in the region. Small streams flow down the Rocky Mountains in this region and thus make it a fertile tract of land. Sal and bamboo trees can be noticed all over the place. Palamu provides a wonderful opportunity for wildlife and nature lovers, hikers and motorists to explore the world. There are many forests bungalows and is a perfect camping site. The climate of the destination stays pleasant and dry during winter. The best time to visit this place is between the months of October to March, as the climate of Palamu is tropical and the winters stays mild and dry. Palamu district endowed with a lush topography; imperial Sal forests and congenial ambiance attract flocks of tourists.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Palamu has 3 and 4 star hotels, lodges and Tourism Bungalows. One can also reserve rooms in Tourism Bungalows run by the Jharkhand Tourism Office in Daltonganj which is just 25 kms away. Tourists visiting the Forest Reserve or the sanctuaries of Palamu, can book for an accommodation in the Reserve itself. The Reserve has tourist bungalows, cottages and rooms for those interested to stay the night.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport to Palamu city is at Ranchi, which is at a distance of 141 kms. Ranchi is well connected to Delhi, Calcutta, Patna and Lucknow by regular flights.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Railway</strong> - The nearest important railway station to Palamu railway station is at Daltonganj which is 30 kms and takes half an hour to reach Palamu from Daltonganj railway station. Daltonganj station is well connected to Ranchi and many other important cities of India.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - There are many Jharkhand State Road transport buses or the Palamu State road buses or the Bihar State road transport buses that ply between Ranchi, Daltonganj and Patna.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By River</strong> - Palamu is well connected via rivers. In areas where there are no bridges, the rivers are crossed on foot if possible. During the rainy season ferries also ply. As most of the connecting Ghats have not yet been connected with bridges, there are ferries that connect Palamu to other areas.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - State buses and private buses are available to travel to and within the city. Other than that, people travel within the city by sharing taxies, jeeps and autos. When going to nearby places, tourists can also commute by cycle rickshaws.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - PALAMU - (FAMOUS FOR BHUTTE KI KHEES, &nbsp;DAL BHAFLA, JALEBI, SEEHH KEBAB, KHURMA, SHRIKHAND, POHA MALPUA, CHOLA BURGER &nbsp;GULAB JAMMUN AND BOPHALI PAAN)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(339, 14, 31, 741, 'Jharkhand', 'INDIA', 'SAHIBGANJ', 'diya-1782403_6401.jpg', 'diya-1782403_6402.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Sahibganj district is one of the districts of Jharkhand state and Sahibganj is the administrative headquarters of this district. It is surrounded by Pakaur district from south, Godda district from west, Katihar &amp; Bhagalpur district of Bihar state from north, Maldah and Murshidabad district of West Bengal state from east. Sahibganj means a place of masters. Rajmahal, a place located in the district was made the capital of Bengal Subah in 1592 by Raja Man Singh, a general of the Mughal Emperor Akbar for the first time. It again became the capital of Bengal Subah in 1639, when Shah Shuja was appointed the Subahdar and it remained so till 1660. The river Ganges forming the northern boundary of the Sahibganj district enters at its north western corner and journeys eastward up to Sakrigali where it takes a turn to the south and forms the southern boundary of the Sahibganj district. Sahibganj is only one District of Jharkhand, which contains Ganga River.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Sahibganj has limited number of hotels but with excellent arrangements in each of them. Though there are no star rated luxury hotels present here but there are budgeted hotels with all necessary facilities required for a comfortable stay.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest airport to Sahibganj is Patna in Bihar state which is 324 kms away. The airport of Ranchi, Jharkhand is 419 kms from Sahibganj.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Sahibganj is well connected through its railway station with various major cities in the country. The Sahibganj Junction Railway Junction lies on the Bhagalpur Rampurhat rail route.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Sahibganj lies on NH 80 between Maharajpur and Kahalgaon and has a good network of State roads that connect it to every remote corner of the district. What is appealing is that the Jamtara Dumka Sahibganj road also provides a link to the state of Assam after a short ferry across the Ganges from Sahibganj.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water </strong>- There are ferry services that ply across the river between the ghats of Sahibganj and the Manihari ghats of the Katihar district, the Rajmahal ghat in the Sahibganj district and Manikchak ghat in the Maldah district of West Bengal. Generally there are country boats that ply in the river between these ghats. One can also find motorized boats plying between the ghats.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - There are taxis and cycle rickshaws to move around the city that one can make use of.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - KABUL MISTHAN BHANDAR, LOCATED IN SAHIBGANJ - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA, MASALA DHOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - MAHARAJA SWEETS, LOCATED AT BATA ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR CHAT ITEMS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - SAHIBGANJ - {FAMOUS FOR DHUSKA IS A SNACK MADE FROM BASMATI RICE BATTER AND CHANA DAL WITH GREEN CHILLIS AND GARLIC AND THEN FRIED ; ARSA IS A SWEET MADE FROM RICE AND JAGGERY ; THEKUA IS A DESERT MADE FROM WHEAT FLOUR, SUGAR SYRUP OR JAGGERY, GHEE, CARDAMOM}</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(340, 14, 31, 741, 'Jharkhand', 'INDIA', 'SIMDEGA', 'india-1129953_640.jpg', 'india-1129953_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Simdega is one of the prominent cities of Jharkhand and is headquarter of Simdega district. Simdega was originally aligned to Ghumla district but was curved out of it on 30th April 2001. Located in the southern western division of the Indian state Jharkhand, the region is quite close to the capital city of the state, Ranchi which lies at a distance of 170 kms and Rourkela which is a part of Odisha at a distance of 77 kms. Simdega district is also a part of Red Corridor which implies considerable Naxalite Maoist rebellion in this area. Simdega is a town and the district headquarters of the Simdega district in Jharkhand. This is a true place where one gets to see and experience the life of tribes. Though Simdega is slowly evolving as a semi township, it still holds on to the fresh flavour of nature. The place is inhabited by Adivasis and the visitor come here to enjoy the local flavour of the place and to enjoy the scenic beauty as Simdega rests amidst plush greenery like forests where camping and other activities are also not uncommon. Simdega has a few beautiful attractions worth visiting. The Kelaghagh Dam is one among them. The dam is surrounded by an array of hills that makes it a breathtaking sight. The other major attractions of Simdega include Ramrekha Dham, Dangadi, Ketunga Dham, Bhanwar Pahar and Mazar of Anjar Peer Sahib.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Simdega is a small city with moderate to basic accommodation facilities. Simdega also has a circuit house and a government run tourist lodge.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport to Simdega is in Ranchi which is about 162 kms from the Simdega.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train </strong>- Rourkela Railway Station in Orissa is the nearest railhead to Simdega. From here tourists can get trains to all the major cities in the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Commuting from the nearby cities is easy for travellers as buses are available from cities like Ranchi, Gumla, Lohardaga, Sasaram and Rourkela.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(341, 14, 31, 751, 'Punjab', 'INDIA', 'SHAHEED BHAGAT SINGH NAGAR (NAWANSHAHAR)', 'yoga-381653_640.jpg', 'yoga-381653_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Shaheed Bhagat Singh Nagar district formerly known as Nawanshahr district is one of the districts in Doaba region of the state of Punjab. Nawanshehr has become a popular tourist destination over the years, owing to its picturesque surroundings and pleasant year-round climate. The presence of the River Sutlej greatly enhances the beauty and fertility of the land. Nawanshehr, earlier known as Nausar, was named after the Afghan military chief Nausher Khan, who built it during the reign of Alauddin Khilji. In the year 2008, Punjab Chief Minister S. Parkash Singh Badal officially changed the name of Nawanshehr to Shahid Bhagat Singh Nagar. Nawanshehr tourism is highly rewarding as tourist attractions of the destination can keep visitors engrossed for days. Among the most prominent tourist attractions are the five forts or havelis, which were built by Nausher Khan. Nawanshehr experiences hot summers, cold winters and humid monsoons. An ideal time for Nawanshehr tourism is from October through March, mainly comprising the winter season.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Nawanshahr offers its visitors a wide variety of accommodation options to choose from. These include all the home stays, economy hotels and lavish five star hotels and lodges to guesthouses. The tariff could range between Rs 2500 to Rs 300 per single room ranging from top of the line hotel to a budget hotel depending on full boarding or room only basis.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Sahnewal airport at Ludhiana is the nearest airport to Nawanshahr, located at a distance of 54 kms.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Nawanshahr railway station is in the centre of the town. Nawanshahr railway station is well connected with Jalandhar and Phagwara railway stations.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Nawanshahr is situated on State Highway 18 of Punjab, and well connected with all major cities of Punjab such as Ludhiana, Phagwara Jalandhar etc.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Patiala and East Punjab States Union and Punjab roadways run several bus services to Nawanshahr from all major cities of Punjab such as Jalandhar, Ludhiana and Phagwara etc.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', '');
