(342, 14, 31, 733, 'Assam', 'INDIA', 'SILCHAR', 'railroad-179278_640.jpg', 'railroad-179278_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Silchar, the headquarters of Cachar district in Assam, is one of the must-visit places in the state. The reason for this is the large number of tourist attractions that it offers to the visitors. Right from natural beauty to architectural splendour, you will find the tourist places in Silchar to offer a large variety. In this article, we have provided a list of the famous tourist attractions of Silchar. Go through it and explore each of the attractions in detail. Silchar has many tourist spots. There are temples and places of historical significance in Silchar. Situated on the Surma River, and known for its scenic beauty and natural splendour, Silchar is surrounded by Manipur on the east, Bangladesh on the west, Mizoram on the south and the Barail hills on the north. The place derived its name from two words: shil and char, meaning rocky fields. Silchar is the 2nd largest town of Assam and is one of the most stable areas in the north east and hence locally referred as the Island of Peace. It is also one of the most developed areas with its own airport and institutes of higher education. Due to its picturesque location, Silchar is also used as the gateway to the neighboring areas of Manipur and Mizoram. Approximately 90% residents of Silchar are Bengalis who speak the Sylheti dialect, the rest being Bishnupriya Manipuri, Dimasa Kachari, Manipuri, Marwaris, Assamese and some tribal groups like Nagas. Silchar is popularly known as Barak Valley.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Government operated &lsquo;Prashaanti Tourist Lodge&rsquo; is the most economical place to stay in Silchar. This place offers basic but comfortable accommodation and their contact info is given above. Other small to midsized hotels are also there in Silchar which caters to the large sized business community that visits Silchar throughout the year.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Flight</strong> - The Silchar Airport is connected to many major cities like Guwahati, Kolkata, Imphal, Tezpur and Agartala through Air India, Air India Regional and Jet Airways. The second nearest Domestic Airport from Silchar is Imphal Airport, 264 kms from Silchar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Silchar is very well connected through Assam State Road Transport Corporation (ASRTC) and various private bus operators. Taxis are also easily available and are probably one of the best modes of transport in the northeast if budget allows.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Silchar has its own railway station located in the Tarapur area, but it has only metre gauge currently. It is connected with most of the important places of northeast including Guwahati, Lunding, Agartala, etc. The other nearest Railway Station is Badarpur Railway Station, located at a distance of 32 kms from Silchar. It is very well connected to many major cities like Dimapur and Guwahati. The railway link from Silchar to Lumding is one of the most picturesque railway routes in India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - To travel around the tourist places in Silchar one can hire local cab available in the city. There are private taxi services in the city. However, one must get the rates fixed in advance. Hiring a taxi would probably be advisable to move around the city of Silchar.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - NAWAB RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT OPPOSITE ISLAIL LARKET, CENTRAL ROAD, TARAPUR - (FAMOUS FOR BIRIYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - MARWARI DHABA, LOCATED AT KARILGANJ-SILCHAR ROAD, BAJANTIPUR - (FAMOUS FOR PARATHA AND PANEER MAKHANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - SOUTH CORNER, LOCATED AT RANGIRKHARI, CENTRAL ROAD, ALBICAPATTY - (FAMOUS FOR SOUTH INDIAN DISHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - RADHA MADHAB MISTANNA BHANDER, LOCATED AT LULDING - SILCHAR ROAD, TARAPUR - (FAMOUS FOR KAJU BARFI AND DRY FRUITS LADDU)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - YO LOLOS, LOCATED AT ALBICAPATTY - (FAMOUS FOR MOMOS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - PARATA PATTI, LOCATED AT TARAPUR - (FAMOUS FOR PARATHA&#39;S)<br />\r\n&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(343, 14, 31, 757, 'West Bengal', 'INDIA', 'SIRAMPUR (AKA) NAHAN', 'buffalo-195584_640.jpg', 'buffalo-195584_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Away from the buzzing crowd of the city, Nahan is a perfect romantic getaway. Lying among the lofty Shivalik range overlooking lush green fields, dirt free roads and clean streets, this small hill station serves as an ideal holiday destination. Nahan has its past spun around many tales and legends. Founded by Raja Karan Prakash in 1621 as a capital, it is believed that this town derives its name from a sage named Nahar who lived at the same site where this town stands today. As per another version, the town gets its name from an incident where the king who was trying to kill a lion was stopped by a saint named Baba Banwari Das who said Nahar meaning &#39;don&#39;t kill&#39;. The quaint town today, is dotted with gardens, temples and a manmade lake.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Nahan is a small town where one will never have problem with accommodation. With several tourist attractions offered by the destination, it also offers hotels and resorts varying from economical to deluxe and premium range. With several facilities and services, tourists can also expect good food, ambience and hospitality.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air</strong> - Dehradun and Chandigarh are the nearest air bases, located at a distance of 100 kms from Nahan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Rail</strong> - Ambala is the nearest railway station that is situated at a distance of 71 kms from Nahan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Road</strong> - Travellers interested in exploring Nahan can visit the destination by bus. Nahan is accessible from various kinds of luxurious buses, connecting it to nearby places like Delhi, Shimla, and Kullu.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Commuting within the town of Nahan is not difficult. Taxis and cabs are readily available for nearby and distant locations. The roads to Nahan town are quite smooth; however, the case within town may differ.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(344, 14, 31, 739, 'Haryana', 'INDIA', 'SIRSA', 'india-1545831_640.jpg', 'india-1545831_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">The Sirsa district derives its name from its headquarters Sirsa. The district is believed to be one of the oldest places of North India. Sirsa finds mention in Mahabharata; however at that time it was known as Sairishaka. The place is also mentioned in Panini&#39;s Ashatadhayayi and Divyavadan. In Mahabharata, it is mentioned that Sairishaka was taken by Nakula in his conquest of the western quarter. Panini has mentioned that Sirsa was a flourishing city in the 5th century BC. Sirsa is one of the districts of Haryana state and is located on the National Highway 10. In 1819, the territory was taken over by the British, and later it became a part of the North western district of the Delhi territory. A year later, the North western district was divided into Northern and Western districts and Sirsa became part of Western district, which was later renamed Haryana. The district of Sirsa has much to offer its visitors. Sirsa is the headquarters of Dera Sacha Sauda, a religious group founded by Shah Mastana, whose actual name was Khemamal. The sect is known for its social services activities and offers free langar and does not accept any donation from the public. Another very popular religious sect, Radha Swami Sect also has its base here. Radha Swami Satsang Ghar is situated close to the village Sikandar Pur, five kilometres to the east of Sirsa city. Sirsa enjoys a sub tropical climate with three distinct seasons: summer, monsoon and winters.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Sirsa draws in a regular tourist crowd, and several of the hotel establishments cater to travelling businessmen. Amenities like 24 hour air conditioning, room service, laundry service and electricity back up are fairly standard across all the hotels.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Road</strong> - Sirsa is also well connected by road which connects all the major cities and states.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport is the Indira Gandhi International Airport, New Delhi which is about 250 kms from Sirsa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Private and HSRTC operated buses available frequently from other cities and states to reach the city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Train</strong> - Sirsa has its own railway station which is well connected to all major cities and states.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Sirsa has abundant rickshaws and auto rickshaws, making for a very well interconnected city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(345, 14, 31, 733, 'Assam', 'INDIA', 'SIVASAGAR/SIBSAGAR', 'highway-332361_6402.jpg', 'H14.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Sibsagar, also known as Sivasagar literally translates to the ocean of Lord Shiva. Sibsagar is the district headquarters of the same name and is 360 kilometres from the state capital Guwahati. It is a historical town as it was the capital of the Ahom kingdom for about 100 years. There is a 129 acre artificial tank called the Sibsagar Tank around which the town is built. The presence of historical monuments belonging to the Ahom times is considered the pride of the town. Today Sibsagar has grown from being merely a historical town and with oil and tea gardens surrounding it, there is a lot to explore in this Upper Assam tourist destination. The Ahoms ruled the Assam region for over 600 years until they were completely wiped out by the Burmese in the year 1817. The kingdom was later annexed to the British. Sibsagar was divided into three sub divisions by the British for administrative purpose.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Sivasagar has several accommodation options to choose from. There are hotels, lodges and guest houses to suit every budget here. There is also a Circuit House and a Government run Tourist Lodges here. There are many decent accommodation facilities in Sibsagar. Budget lodges to good hotels everything is available here.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Sibsagar does not have any airport within the city. The nearest airport is at Jorhat, located about 55 kilometres away. The airport has regular flights to Guwahati, Kolkata and Silchar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The nearest railhead to Sibsagar is at Simalguri that is located about 16 kilometres from the town. This railway station falls in between the Guwahati Dibrugarh rail line and thus many trains stop here.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - The National Highway 37 runs through Sibsagar and continues till Dibrugarh further up in the state. The NH has been the major route for tea traders and oil exporters and till today is a very busy highway. The town is thus well connected to the other parts of the state as well as the region.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Auto rickshaws and cabs might be available.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SAIKIA FAST FOOD, LOCATED IN SIVASAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR CHOLA-BHOTORA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - FRIENDS FASTFOOD AND RESTAURANT, LOCATED IN SIVASAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR PARATHA, CHICKEN CURRY AND ROLLS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - FLAVOURZZZ, LOCATED AT GNG ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA AND SNACKS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - BLACK PEPPER, LOCATED ON AT ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR MOMOS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - SIVASAGAR - {FAMOUS FOR LAKSA IS A TYPE OF NOODLE SOUP MADE FROM VERMICELLI, COCONUT MILK, CURRY SOUP BASE}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(347, 14, 31, 739, 'Haryana', 'INDIA', 'SONIPAT', 'lohri-654481_640.jpg', 'lohri-654481_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">A perfect picnic package for visitors, Sonepat, widely known as Sonipat is the district headquarters of the Sonepat district of Haryana. At just 30 kms from the border of New Delhi, it lies under the National Capital Region area and is surrounded by the River Yamuna on its eastern side. Being close to New Delhi, the place enjoyed special attention from Mughal rulers and the evidence of the same can be seen in the architectural structures present in the city. Sonipat Travel Guide is incomplete without a mention of its rich cultural and spiritual legacy. Temples, Mosque of Abdullah Nasir ud din and Khwaja Khizr Tomb are the famous tourist attractions worth visiting in the city. It is believed that Sonepat was one of the five &ldquo;Prasthas&rdquo; demanded by the Pandavas from Duryodhana. In those days it was known as Swarna Prastha and this gave way to its current name Sonepat or Sonipat meaning the &ldquo;Golden City&rdquo;.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Sonipat has some deluxe and medium to budget accommodation options.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Sonipat is very well connected by road network with various cities and states.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport is Indira Gandhi International Airport, New Delhi about 45 kms from Sonipat.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Haryana State Road Transport Corporation (HSRTC) and private travel services are easily available to reach Sonipat from all other major cities and neighbouring states.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Sonipat has its own railway station which connects all major cities of the state and neighbouring states also.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - BTW RESTAURANT &amp; CAFE, LOCATED AT VARDHMAN COMPLEX, SECTOR 13, OSRAM CHOWK - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;AALOO TIKKI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - GULSHAN DHABA, LOCATED AT 49-50 MILESTONE, GT ROAD, MURTHAL, SONIPAT - (FAMOUS FOR STUFFED PARATHA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - PUNJABI TADKA, LOCATED AT INDIRA COLONY, ATLAS ROAD, MUNICIPAL COLONY, ASHOK NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR SAHAI PANEER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - R.K. SWEETS&amp;NAMKEEN, LOCATED AT ATLAS ROAD, MUNICIPAL COLONY, ASHOK NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA, BARFI, GULABJAMUN, MILKCAKE AND GHEWAR)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - PYARE LAL, LOCATED AT NEAR GUR MANDI, ROHTAK ROAD, AGGARSAIN NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR PEDE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - BHASKAR SWEET SHOP, LOCATED AT VIJAY NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR GAZAR KA HALWA AND BARFI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - BURFIWALA, LOCATED AT NATIONAL HIGHWAY 1, MURTHAL - (FAMOUS FOR KHOYA BARFI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n8 - RAJU FIROZABADI, LOCATED AT SHOP NO.156 SECTOR 14 - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA AND GULAB JAMUN)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(348, 14, 31, 733, 'Assam', 'INDIA', 'SONITPUR', 'tea-garden-1580758_640.jpg', 'tea-garden-1580758_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Sonitpur is an administrative district in the state of Assam in India. The district headquarters are located at Tezpur. As of 2011 it is the third most populous district of Assam after Nagaon and Dhubri. Sonitpur district was created in 1983 when it was split from Darrang. Sonitpur district is home to 73 tea gardens including world&#39;s biggest tea garden, Monabari. A visit to a tea garden provides insight not only into tea making and the unique culture associated with it but also gives the flavour of bygone era of the Raj.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><u><strong>Tezpur</strong></u></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Tezpur, Sonitpur&#39;s largest town and the largest urban centre on the northern bank of the Brahmaputra is located 180 kms northeast of Guwahati. It is considered the cultural capital of Assam. Located in the state of Assam, Tezpur is a beautiful city full of breathtaking sceneries and serene spots. Tourists flock the region in pursuit of peace and tranquillity. It is a municipal board of Sonitpur district and also its administrative headquarters. Being a very ancient city, it is widely known as the &quot;Cultural Capital of Assam&rdquo; and is nestled beautifully on the banks of the River Brahmaputra. Tezpur offers numerous interesting attractions to its visitors. The city is resplendent with picturesque views and innate serene beauty. The tourists flock the place to enjoy and absorb the beauty of some of its scenic attractions such as Kalia Bhomora Setu, Bura Chapori Wildlife Sanctuary and Nameri National Park etc. It has given immense contribution in the field of art, literature and culture in the history of Assam. Geographically Tezpur has been blessed with the plains, the mountain views and a mighty river. Nature has been abundant here. While the Brahmaputra never fails to impress one and all, the Kolia Bhomora Bridge which is a 3015 mts long connecting the Sonitpur district to the Nagaon district is impressive in its own way.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Tezpur having been a prominent British Colonial Commercial Town and currently a major tourist spot in Assam is well equipped with luxury and budget hotels to suit all types of travellers even foreign businessmen. Big branded hotels offer plush ambience and amenities and budget hotels and government run lodges such as the tourist lodge, dak bungalow, circuit house and Arunachal government guest house which offer clean and comfortable accommodation.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - Also known as the &lsquo;Salonibari Airport&rsquo;, the Tezpur Airport which is 9 kms north from the city square has connecting Flights to Guwahati, Silchar and Kolkata.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train </strong>- 5 kms south of the Tezpur city centre on the west bank of River Brahmaputra is the Tezpur Railway Station which connects to the major Railway Junction in Rangiya which is 150 kms southwest of Tezpur and 50 kms north of Guwahati.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road </strong>- Roadways are lifelines to Tezpur. From Guwahati, there are two routes to reach Tezpur. One is via Mangaldai and Udalbari on the National Highway 52 while the other is via Nagaon on the National Highway 37. In both the routes there are day and night buses available.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Bus </strong>- Daily Assam State Transport Corporation (ASTC) Buses and mini buses ply between Guwahati and Tezpur. In Tezpur, the ASTC Bus Stand is on Tezpur Main Road within walking distance from the Taxi Stand.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - KF RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT MISSION CHARIALI, NH 52, TEZPUR - (FAMOUS FOR MANCHURIAN, FRIED RICE AND MOMOS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - CAFE WOODBOX, LOCATED AT PATIACHUBRI, TEZPUR - (FAMOUS FOR KEBABS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - KRISHNA FOODS, LOCATED AT MISSION CHARIALI, KETEKIBARI, TEZPUR - (FAMOUS FOR PURI SABJI)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(349, 14, 31, 738, 'gujarat', 'INDIA', 'SURAT', 'sea-326986_640.jpg', 'sea-326986_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Surat holds a significant place not only from the industrial and commercial point of view but also from the point of view of tourism. Surat is located close to the Arabian Sea and enjoys a mild climate round the year. In the 14th century, the Mughals made this city an important part of their reign. There are a few exotic beaches in Surat that it rightly brags of. This lovely place is located on the banks of the river Tapi and is famous for the silk fabrics, brocades and the diamond cutting works. Surat is visited by a large number of tourists from the different parts of India and abroad. All these people come here lured by the tourist attractions in Surat. Ranging from castles to the cemeteries and from the mausoleum to the museums, there are many things to watch around in Surat. A tourist will simply fall short of his vacations as there is no end to the Surat tourist attractions. There are several monuments, museums and gardens in Surat that are known for their own distinct charm and grandeur. The tour to Surat has a lot in store for the travel freak. It offers every opportunity to the tourist to come and have a flavour of the true Gujarati hospitality and cuisine as well. &#39;Diamond Hub of the World&#39;, &#39;Embroidery capital of India&#39;, &#39;Textile City of India&#39; as it is proudly called; Surat is the fastest growing city in the world and a powerful magnet for fashion moguls, art lovers and diamond dealers. In the mid 15th century, Surat was one of the India&#39;s most important port cities. Despite many historical travails and battles, the city retains an intriguing medieval charm. Historic romanticism, along with the coastal graciousness, is what makes Surat an important tourist destination in Gujarat. One can see the footprints of the city in the epic novel, Mahabharat, as per which Lord Krishna had a brief stopover in Surat when he was going to Dwarka, from Mathura.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The accommodation options in Surat city range from luxury 5 to 3 star hotels, pet friendly hotels, lodges and guest houses, last minutes hotels, budget and small hotels. Accommodation here is easily available and sits well in budget. Due its prominence as a business hub and second largest city of Gujarat, one will hardly find any problem for booking a stay in Surat. Most hotels offer facilities like free wifi, conference rooms, business centres, meeting rooms, board rooms, conference spaces and state of the art technologies are all available here, which makes them perfect for the business travellers. From 5 stars to mid range, Surat offers multiple types of accommodations that suit every topic.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Surat has its own airport. It is a domestic airport and is simply known as Surat Airport. It is well-connected through regular flights with important cities of India such as Delhi, Coimbatore, Goa, Chennai, Indore, Bhopal, Kochi, Bangalore, Kolkata, Aurangabad, Madurai, Ahmedabad, Madurai, Hyderabad and Mumbai.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail</strong> - Located in the city centre, Surat railway station is one of the main stations the Western railways network, on the Vadodara Valsad rail link. The station is place close to the bus stand also. Regular trains connect Surat to important cities of India, via Ahmedabad in Gujarat and Mumbai in Maharashtra.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road -</strong> Surat lies just off the NH 8 that connects Ahmedabad to Mumbai and Surat. A good network of roads connects Surat with surroundings cities. One can either rent a cab or can ride a Gujarat State Road Transport Corporation (GSRTC) and some private bus that plies to important destinations like Delhi, Gujarat, Madhya Pradesh and Maharashtra.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting around Surat </strong>- Buses form an important part of Surat&#39;s transportation scene. The daily commuters in Surat avail the bus services provided by the Government of Gujarat. Taxi is another mode of transport, but the most preferred mode of transportation in Surat is the auto-rickshaw.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SURAT - {FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;KHICHYU IS A TYPE OF SNACK MADE FROM RICE FLOUR, CUMIN, ALKALINE SALT KNOWN AS PAPAD KHAR ; GHARI IS A SWEET DISH MADE FROM GHEE AND DRY FRUIT ; KHAJA IS A DESERT MADE FROM WHEAT FLOUR, SUGAR, OIL ; COLLEGIAN IS A SNACK MADE FROM TOMATOES, ONION AND PEANUTS ; SEV KHAMANI IS A SNACK MADE FROM CHICK-PEA AND WITHCHUTNEY AND SEV ; LOCHO IS A TYPE OF SNACK MADE FROM GRAM FLOUR}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - JALARAM, LOCATED AT KASHI PLAZA, DAYALJI ASHRAM MARG, BESIDE DR. BIPIN DESAI CHILDREN, HOSPITAL, MAJURA GATE - (FAMOUS FOR KHICHADI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - WORLD PLATTER, LOCATED AT 2ND FLOOR, KALA MANDIR JEWELLERS BUILDING, GHOD DOD ROAD, OPPOSITE PIZZA HUT, ATHWA - (FAMOUS FOR PASTA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - TIPSY TOPSY ( H.O ), LOCATED AT KANAKNIDHI SHOPPING COMPLEX, TIMILIYAWAD ROAD, OPPOSITE GANDHI SMRUTI BHAVAN, NANPURA - (FAMOUS FOR GUJARATI THALI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n5 - CRUNCH, LOCATED AT G3, GREEN ELINA BUILDING, ANAND MAHAL ROAD, NAROTAM NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - WAY WAIT RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT KALPANA SOCIETY-2, OPPOSITE VIVEKANAND BRIDGE, ADAJAN ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR SEV TAMATO)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - GEETHA RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT UDHNA MAGDALLA ROAD, VESU CHAR-RASTA,OPP. J. H AMBANI SCHOOL, PIPLOD - (FAMOUS FOR BIRYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>8 - SINGH SAAAB DI RASOI, LOCATED AT PATIALA HOUSE, OPPOSITE NEW PASSPORT OFFICE, NEW UMRA ROAD, PIPLOD - (FAMOUS FOR LASSI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>9 - THE FOOD VALLEY BY PUNJABI KADHAI, LOCATED AT SHOP NO-2, AAGAM EMPORIO, OPOOSITE HERO SHOWROOM, UNIVERSITY ROAD, VESU&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; - (FAMOUS FOR BUTTER CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>10 - KAILESH RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT SHRINATHJI APARTMENT, TIMALIAWAD, NANPURA - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA WITH GREEN CHUTNEY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>11 - GANGOUR VESU, LOCATED AT G-SUKUM PLATINUM, 1, WARD 2, VESU - (FAMOUS FOR PANEER TIKKA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n12 - MUMBAI&#39;S GRILL FAST FOOD, LOCATED AT ASCON CITY SHOP NO. 33, 34, OPPOSITE MAHESHWARI BHAVAN, NEAR SCIENCE CENTRE, CITY LIGHT , ATHWA - (FAMOUS FOR SANDWICHES, PIZZA AND STUFF KULCHA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>13 - SUMMIT RESTAURANT,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT BRIJVASUNDHARA APPT, OPPOSITE BHARAT PETROL PUMP, NEAR JAKAT NAKA, SAROLI - (FAMOUS FOR KHICHADI AND KARI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>14 - MAHESH, LOCATED AT GARDEN VIEW APPARTMENT, HONEY PARK CROSS ROADS, ADAJAN - (FAMOUS FOR PAV BHAJI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>15 - MING KITCHEN, LOCATED AT DUMAS ROAD, KARGIL CHOWK, OPPOSITE SWASTIK HOUSE, PIPLOD - (FAMOUS FOR FRIED RICE AND PANEER CHILLY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>16 - SHREE SAINATH SNACKS, LOCATED AT SHREE SAINATH SNACKS,NEAR CANARA BANK, TIMILIYAWAD ROAD, KHARWAWAD - (FAMOUS FOR MASALA DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>17 - G.DADA FARSAN &amp; SURTI RASOI, LOCATED AT G17, GREEN ATRIA, ANAND MAHAL ROAD, ADAJAN - (FAMOUS FOR CHEESE SAMOSHA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>18 - MOGJI&#39;S, LOCATED AT G6, AQUA CORRIDOR, NEXT TO STAR BAZAAR, ADAJAN - (FAMOUS FOR ROLLS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>19 - BAWARCHI GARDEN RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT GJ SH 169, VANAKALA - (FAMOUS FOR BUTTER PEPPER CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>20 - SAINATH SNACKS &amp; FAST FOOD, LOCATED AT SHREEJI ARCADE, ADAJAN ROAD, ADAJAN GAM, GURU RAM PAVAN BHUMI - (FAMOUS FOR MASALA DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>21 - BHAI BHAI OMELETTE CENTER, LOCATED AT TRIVENI APARTMENT, OPPOSITE LIC OFFICE ,NANPURA MAIN ROAD, TIMALIAWAD, NANPURA - (FAMOUS FOR EGG ROLL AND OMELETTE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>22 - NEW RAMESH MITHAI, LOCATED AT KRISHNA NAGAR, JEEVKAR NAGAR, ATHWA - (FAMOUS FOR LASSI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>23 - MUDITA NI MITHAIO, LOCATED AT SHOP MAHEK, OPPOSITE HIRA MANEK STREET, NANPURA MAIN ROAD, NANPURA - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA AND KACHORI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n24 - 24 CARATS MITHAI MAGIC, LOCATED AT CHAUTA BAZAR RD, CHAUTA PUL, GOPIPUR - (FAMOUS FOR KAJU KATALI AND GHEWAR)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>25 - MANBHAVAN SWEETS &amp; NAMKEENS, LOCATED AT HARI ICHCHHA INDUSTRIAL SOCIETY, JEEVAN JYOTHI NAGAR, UDHNA - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;KAJU KATLI)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(350, 14, 31, 1657, 'Chhattisgarh', 'INDIA', 'SURGUJA', 'hibiscus-1760930_640.jpg', 'hibiscus-1760930_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Surguja lies in the northern part of Chhattisgarh and is bordered by Uttar Pradesh and Jharkhand. 50% of the land is covered by forest which is inhabited by the tribes. Chhattisgarh is the 17th tea producing state in India and Surguja along with Jashpur have the most favourable conditions for producing tea. Mythical stories are related to this place. It is said that Lord Rama visited this place during his exile of fourteen years and therefore there are certain places named after Lord Rama, Goddess Sita and Laxmana. Ramgarh, Sita Bhengra and Laxmangarh are some of them. Like other places of Chhattisgarh, Surguja has also witnessed the rule of various dynasties. Starting with Nandas and Mauryas, it passed on to the Rakshal clan. It was a princely state under the British regime. The Hasdeo River, the Rihand River and the Kanhar River form the river basins of Surguja. Surguja is also famed for being the backdrop of Green Oscar winning movie, The Last Migration which focuses on the elephants of the region.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Surguja is slowly picking up on tourism and one can find quite a few hotels to stay in the main town area.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Surguja by Road</strong> : Buses are readily available from Durg, Bilaspur and Raipur. Private taxi or car service can also transport to various tourist spots of Surguja.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Surguja by Train</strong> : Trains are available up to Ambikapur in Surguja district. It is about 230 kms from Bilaspur. An overnight train is available which runs between Durg and Ambikapur in Surguja district.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Surguja by Air</strong> : Surguja is 375 kms from Raipur Airport, which is the nearest. Flights to major cities are available from Raipur.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - PANCHSHEEL MANPASAND BAKERY AND RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT BESIDE SBI COLLECTORATE BRANCH, DEVIGANJ ROAD, KEDARPUR, AMBIKAPUR - (FAMOUS FOR CAKES AND PASTERIES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - CAFE MARINE DRIVE FOOD POINT, LOCATED AT CAFE MARINE DRIVE FOOD POINT, FIRST FLOOR, PRATAPPUR ROAD, AMBIKAPUR - (FAMOUS FOR MASALA DOSA, PANEER PAKAUDA AND MASALA COLDRINK)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - KATHI JUNCTION, LOCATED AT AMBIKAPUR - (FAMOUS FOR ROLLS)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(351, 14, 31, 1659, 'Manipur', 'INDIA', 'TAMENGLONG', 'sun-365981_640.jpg', 'sun-365981_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">A hilly district, Tamenglong is all hills, valleys and ranges. The beautiful district of Tamenglong is one of the nine districts of Manipur. Tamenglong is a marvellous district full of natural and cultural diversity. Home to rare orchids, virgin forests, rare species of birds and animals, Tamenglong is also known as the Land of the Hornbill. Tamenglong is situated in the west of Manipur and is bounded by Senapati district in the east and north, Churachandpur in the south and Imphal West and some parts of Assam in the west. According to the 2011 census, Tamenglong is the least populous district of Manipur. In between the hills and ranges, small hamlets dot the valleys increasing the mystic beauty of the place. The topography of Tamenglong consists of sandstone, schist and shale making the soil and rocks weak. The result is that Tamenglong experiences regular landslides. Deep gorges, mysterious caves, splendid waterfalls and exotic orchids are what tourists will find in this district headquarters of Tamenglong District. The Tharon cave, Buning meadow, Zilad lakes, Barak Waterfalls are some of the places of tourist interest. Rongmei, Lengmei, Zemei Nagas are dominant tribes of Tamenglong. This beautiful place is located at a distance of 156 kms from Imphal.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Tamenglong does not offer many accommodation options to travellers as it is still an unexplored tourist destination. However, travellers can look for accommodation options in Imphal and surrounding areas. Tamenglong is just a day trip from Imphal. October to March is the best visit time to visit Tamenglong.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air</strong> -The Imphal Airport is the nearest airhead to Tamenglong. Imphal is 158 kilometres from Tamenglong while the airport is situated 8 kilometres from the capital city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Rail</strong> - Since Manipur doesn&rsquo;t have a railhead, the nearest railway station is at Dimapur. To reach Tamenglong, tourists will need to break the journey via Imphal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Road</strong> - National Highway 53 and National Highway 39 connect Manipur to the rest of the country. To reach Tamenglong, tourists will need to travel on NH 53 via the Old Cachar Road and the Tamenglong Khongsang Road. The state highways also reach Tamenglong from Imphal and are served by the state transport buses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- It&#39;s a small town and hence people can walk on foot or take cycle rickshaws.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(352, 14, 31, 751, 'Punjab', 'INDIA', 'TARN TARAN', 'dd2.jpg', 'dd5.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Tarn Taran is a city, municipal council and administrative district headquarters of Tarn Taran district, situated in the north western region of India, Punjab. It is also known as Tarn Taran Sahib. The area of the town is 5059 sq kms. &nbsp;It is located at an average elevation of 226.5 mts from the mean sea level. Tarn Taran Sahib is surrounded by Amritsar in the north, Kapurthala and Jalandhar in the south east, Faridkot and Kotkapura in the south, Ferozepur in the south west and Pakistan in the west regions respectively. The city Tarn Taran Sahib is named after Sri Darbar Sahib Tarn Taran Gurudwara, which was founded during 15th century by Shri Guru Arjan Dev Ji the 5th Sikh Guru. The city of Tarn Taran is one of the most prominent cities of Punjab and one of the major developmental blocks of Tarn Taran district. Agriculture is the backbone and the main occupation of the town. The main crops of this region are Wheat, Paddy, grams, barley, maize, bajra, sugarcane and cotton. The region has abundant irrigation facilities provided by the Upper Bari Doab canal. A large Industrial area is located in south of Tarn Taran city. The city has many ancient Gurudwaras and is prominent as the hub of Gurudwaras. A sarovar situated in the centre of this town is very popular and the largest holy Sikh Sarovars in the globe. The grain market of Tarn Taran located in the heart of the town is the India&rsquo;s largest grain market.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The city of Tarn Taran does not provide any convenient and comfortable accommodation for the travellers. However, tourists who visit this town can stay in the hotels of Amritsar, which is located about 24 kms from the town. The city of Amritsar offers wide range of accommodation facilities. It offers both luxury and budget accommodation, travellers can choose to stay in the accommodations available as per their budget.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Nearest airport is Raja Sansi and Ludhiana airport which is around 25 and 120 kms from Tarn Taran.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Tarn Taran Sahib has a Railway Station, located in the eastern region of the town near grain market. It is located at about 1.5 kms from Tarn Taran Bus Stand. Tarn Taran Railway Station belongs to northern railways and is connected by broad gauge railway lines.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Tarn Taran is on National Highway 15. By roadways, the city of Tarn Taran is well connected to all other major cities of Punjab and North India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Tarn Taran has a Bus Stand, located in the north eastern region of the town. It has both public and private bus services at regular intervals to intercity and interstate regions. PRTC, PEPSU Road Transport Corporation, PUNBUS and other Private buses provide bus services to the town.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - MAVEN, LOCATED AT SARHALI ROAD, MOHALLA BHAG SHAH - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - REPUBLIC OF CHICKEN, LOCATED AT OBC BANK BUILDING, NEAR BOHRI VLA CHOWK, BARNALA-AMRITSAR BYPASS ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;ROASTED CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - ROYAL ORCHID FOOD PLAZA, LOCATED AT MOGA-AMRITSAR MAIN ROAD , HARIKE PATTAN - (FAMOUS FOR ALOO KULCHA, DAL TADKA, DAHI KADHI, JEERA RICE AND LASSI)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(353, 14, 31, 1660, 'Arunachal Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'TAWANG', 'chingtienkang-1784872_1280.jpg', 'chingtienkang-1784872_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Located in the state of Arunachal Pradesh, Tawang is one of the very beautiful cities to visit and is resplendent with breathtaking sceneries and serene spots. The city is abode to the Monpa tribe and shares its border with Sela range in the east, Tibet in north and Bhutan in the southwest. Tourists flock the region in pursuit of peace and tranquillity. It is widely believed that the city has got its name from one of the most ancient and the biggest Buddhist monasteries in the country, Tawang Monastery and the name &lsquo;Twang&rsquo; is a combination of &lsquo;Ta&#39; meaning Horse and &#39;Wang&#39; meaning Chosen. Located at a height of about 3048 mts, is known for many important and beautiful monasteries and is famous as the birth place of Dalai Lama. The beautiful town of Tawang, also pronounced as Dawang has many sceneries to make your trip a picturesque one. However, what begins to define the area is its significance for Buddhist monks. Tawang is the place to go for monasteries, with the Tawang Monastery being the most popular one and extremely sacred for the Buddhists. Tawang is a place which flatters with its natural beauty wrapped in the scent of spirituality. One can have their taste buds too have an experience of Tawang by indulging into the area&#39;s unique cuisine.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Located in the state of Arunachal Pradesh, Tawang is one of the very beautiful cities to visit and is resplendent with breathtaking sceneries and serene spots. The city is abode to the Monpa tribe and shares its border with Sela range in the east, Tibet in north and Bhutan in the southwest. Tourists flock the region in pursuit of peace and tranquillity. It is widely believed that the city has got its name from one of the most ancient and the biggest Buddhist monasteries in the country, Tawang Monastery and the name &lsquo;Twang&rsquo; is a combination of &lsquo;Ta&#39; meaning Horse and &#39;Wang&#39; meaning Chosen. Located at a height of about 3048 mts, is known for many important and beautiful monasteries and is famous as the birth place of Dalai Lama. The beautiful town of Tawang, also pronounced as Dawang has many sceneries to make your trip a picturesque one. However, what begins to define the area is its significance for Buddhist monks. Tawang is the place to go for monasteries, with the Tawang Monastery being the most popular one and extremely sacred for the Buddhists. Tawang is a place which flatters with its natural beauty wrapped in the scent of spirituality. One can have their taste buds too have an experience of Tawang by indulging into the area&#39;s unique cuisine.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The Tezpur Airport is the best and the closest option for those who are arriving by air. The place is connected by flights from cities such as Kolkata, Delhi and Guwahati.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail</strong> - Rangapara in Assam is the nearest rail head from Tawang and Tezpur is the major railway station.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Tawang is well connected to nearby cities like Guwahati and Tezpur and buses are available for Tawang from Tezpur and other parts of the region.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - The sightseeing within the town can be completed in half a day, and it is best to book a taxi for that. The other section of sightseeing involves moving outside the town. A vehicle like Sumo would be more suited for the purpose. One day is enough to cover these sights, although the roads are not in excellent shape.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - TAWANG,ARUNACHAL PRADESH - {FAMOUS FOR GYAPA KHAZI(BIRYANI) ; &nbsp;RONGPU TAKENG ( EGG CHUTNEY), CHOP THE EGGS, GRATED GINGER AND SALT, BLEND EVERYTHING AS A &nbsp;PASTE ; DONGPO IS A DIH MADE FROM PORK, GINGER, SOY SAUCE, VINEGAR, AND WHITE SUGAR ; KHURA IS A TYPE OF PANCAKE MADE FROM BUCHWHEATFLOUR AND BUTTER}</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(354, 14, 31, 1653, 'Uttarakhand', 'INDIA', 'TEHRI GARHWAL', 'mountians-984112_640.jpg', 'm22.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The Hindu Mythology and legends seemed to have showered Tehri Garhwal with several spiritual significances. It is this place where River Ganga arrives in its real form at Devprayag where River Bhagirathi and River Alaknanda merge. One can also see many temples dotted across the place. In fact the Tehri Garhwal derives its name from the word Triharia which indicates a place where three kinds of sins can be cleared that are result of Mansa, Vacha and Kamana i.e. thought, word and deed respectively. New Tehri, the headquarters of the district is one of the only planned towns of Uttarakhand. Situated at an altitude of 1550-1950 mts above the sea level, it overlooks at the massive lake and equally impressive dam also serves as the major attraction of the area. The Old Tehri that was once heavily inhabited today lies under the water in ruins. Visiting this place is an experience that is worth remembering. According to records, Tehri was the capital of the princely state of Tehri Garhwal, during the British reign. In the 18th century, Tehri served as an important port, where the East India Company halted its ships.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">When it comes to accommodation, the place has got as many options as one can think of. From luxury hotels to mid range and budget hotels and guest houses are available here. Almost each accommodation offers splendid views of Himalayas. HPTDC owned guest houses are also there in various part of the area.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- The Jolly Grant Airport at Dehradun is the nearest airbase, located at a distance of 85 kms from Tehri.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail</strong> - The closest railway station to Tehri is located in Rishikesh, at a distance of 70 kms. This railway station is connected to most of the major Indian cities by frequent trains.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Tourists planning a trip to Tehri can also reach the destination by buses. Luxurious and non-luxurious buses run to Tehri from the Inter State Bus Terminal (ISBT) at Kashmiri Gate, New Delhi. The destination is also connected by regular buses from nearby places like Mussoorie, Rishikesh, Haridwar, Devprayag, Srinagar and Uttarkashi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Tehri is a small town where transportation is available in form of taxis. They are readily available to commute from place to another.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - Tehri Garhwal - [famous for &nbsp;Aalu Ka Jhol(onion and tomato curry base), Kafuli(Made from spinach and fenugreek leafs), Phaanu(mix the different lentils with special Gahat), Baadi( Buck wheat flour), Jhangora Ki Kheer(is sweet by milk, cashews and raisins), Rus/Thhatwani(Prepare by mix lentils and rice paste), Kumaoni Raita(Prepare from curd,cucumber,chillies,mustard seeds) ; famous for Jhangora Ki Kheer(is sweet by milk, cashews and raisins), Singodi(is sweet dish made of Khoya, milk), Arsa(use of jaggery and curd)] &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n', '');
