(355, 14, 31, 739, 'Haryana', 'INDIA', 'KURUKSHETRA', 'electric-power-273648_640.jpg', 'electric-power-273648_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Literally translated, Kurukshetra means the field of righteousness. Kurukshetra tourism is laden with history and mythology. It was here in Kurukshetra that the historic battle of Mahabharata between the Pandavas and Kauravas was fought. It was in this town where Lord Krishna sermonize the sacred Bhagwad Geeta to Arjun. The sacred text preaches about karma and propounds the paramount principles of the Hindu religion. Besides the Bhagwad Geeta, a good number of other sacred texts were also written here. Kurukshetra enjoys a rich and colourful history. With the passage of time, its sacredness only seemed to grow, and it was visited by Lord Buddha&#39; and numerous Sikh gurus all of whom have left an indelible imprint in its rich religious fabric. Today, Kurukshetra tourism stands for unparalleled pilgrimage tours not just for the Hindus but for the Buddhists and Sikhs as well. The town has a large number of devotional centres including holy shrines, temples, Gurudwaras and kunds some of which have their roots in the earliest ages of the Indian civilization.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><u><strong>Thanesar</strong></u></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">A part of district Kurukshetra in Haryana, Thanesar is a historically relevant city. Not just its present but events from the past too have much role to play when talking about Thanesar. From a town which had seen battles, has tales of religious importance along with that of various rulers, Thanesar today is a bustling city. There have been several advancements and much scope not only for the residents of Haryana, but from other cities as well. With good scope for education, Kurukshetra University and National Institute of Technology are part of Thanesar with the city further having a wide industrialisation and cultural prospects. From being a small, quiet village to becoming a modern city, Thanesar has come a long way. In this process there has been a rise in its approach towards tourism which has further contributed to that of the state. The city, which rests on the banks of Sarsawati Ghaggar River, attracts tourists from all parts of the country to witness its historic sites and learn about the culture of this closely knit society. Much of the city is surrounded by beautiful age old temples that has been restored and gather a number of followers each year. Thanesar is also home to some finest museums and historical monuments which stand charming in the heart of the city. The city in its growth is known by its events from the past which are fairly reflected through various elements when going about the city. Situated at a close distance from the capital city, the city&rsquo;s location makes it reachable thus being inviting for tourists throughout the year.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Finding hotels that fits one budget is pretty simple here. Affordable rooms with facilities adding comfort can be found. The basic range of hotels in terms of charges falls between Rs. 500 to Rs. 2000 per night. During the peak season, that is the months between October and March, charges may vary as there is great rush.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Road </strong>- NH 1 connects Chandigarh and Delhi. Road network in Kurukshetra is very good by which all other major cities and states are connected.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport is Chandigarh Airport which is about 75 kms from Kurukshetra.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Bus</strong> - Haryana buses and private buses arrive and depart to various cities from Kurukshetra every minute regularly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - Kurukshetra has its own railway station which connects all neighbouring cities and states.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Getting Around</strong> - Auto rickshaws, taxi and private cabs are the best ways to travel the city. Local bus services are also available here to travel around the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - MASALA BITE SOYA CHAAP SHOP, LOCATED AT SHOP NO 10 RAJENDRA NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR PANEER TIKKA AND KULCHAS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - GULSHAN BHAI, LOCATED AT RAILWAY ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR CHHOLE BHATURE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - DADA&#39;S, LOCATED AT KURUKSHETRA UNIVERSITY - {FAMOUS FOR TEA(CHAI)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - SACHDEVA SWEETS, LOCATED AT STATE HIGHWAY 6, SHANTI NAGAR, THANESAR - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - CHACHA DA PUNJABI DHABA, LOCATED AT SIRSALA - (FAMOUS FOR DAAL MAKHANI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n6 - ANMOL FOOD HUT, LOCATED AT 1/25, KURUKSHETRA, RAILWAY STATION AEA, THANESAR - (FAMOUS FOR SANDWICHES)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(356, 14, 31, 1659, 'Manipur', 'INDIA', 'THOUBAL', 'wood-691629_1280.jpg', 'wood-691629_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">A well developed city, Thoubal is a good holiday destination for those looking for a pleasant climate and numerous activities. Thoubal is almost ideal for trekking, hiking and picnics given the abundance in flora and green landscapes as well as the various facilities available here. This city is most famous for the temples and the numerous water bodies all together making it a pretty much perfect getaway which will strike the right balance of urban and a lesser known destination. Just to add in the environment a dash of activity and vibrancy, are the popular bazaars of the town such as the Ningombam Laxmi Bazaar and Athokpam Bazaar.</p>\r\n', '<p>Budget ranges of hotels are available here for the tourists.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest airport to Thoubal is in the capital of Imphal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail </strong>- Apart from a narrow gauge rail line, Manipur doesn&rsquo;t have a railhead. Thus, the nearest railway station to Thoubal is in Dimapur located 230 kilometres away.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - National Highway 102 passes through Thoubal connecting it to all the important centres of Manipur and India. Additionally the Imphal Moreh Road also connects Thoubal to other parts via NH 39 and NH 53. Apart from state transport buses, private taxis also ply on this route and can easily be availed by tourists.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - It&#39;s a small town and hence people can walk or take cycle rickshaws, taxis and buses.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - Thoubal - (famous for Ooti, Eromba, Ngri, kangshoi)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(357, 14, 31, 733, 'Assam', 'INDIA', 'TINSUKIA', 'ccccc.jpg', 'ccccc1.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The city of Tinsukia in Assam is a commercial hub and serves as an important centre for tourists to commute to other places in Assam. It is also known as the business capital of India and is 480 kms Northeast from Guwahati. Tinsukia, the second largest city of Assam was also known as Changmai Pathar. However its ancient name is Bangmara. It was the capital of Muttack kingdom. There is a triangular shaped pond here known as Tinikunia Pukhri. Being the commercial hub of Assam it produces the best quality of tea and wood products. The major attraction of Tinsukia is Dibru Saikhowa National Park which is a biodiversity hot-spot and is rich in flora and fauna. Tinsukia is quite popular with the tourists as it serves as the gateway to nearby beautiful villages and wildlife sanctuaries. An important town of Assam, it is quite popular with the tourists as well. It also serves as a base place to carry on with holidays to nearby cities. It is almost 500 kms from Guwahati. The history of Tinsukia is both rich and fascinating. The history of Tinsukia reveals interesting and often charming aspects of the culture and life of the people of Tinsukia.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The town isn&#39;t ever too crowded. So getting a room here wouldn&#39;t be too much of a Hassel. During the months of March-October, an air conditioned room will be required. There are many budget lodges in the town. But for those with no monetary restriction, there are plenty of excellent options.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest airport is located in Dibrugarh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail </strong>- Trains can be taken directly to the town of Tinsukia, as the town houses a major railway station.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - National highway 37 connects Tinsukia with rest of the country. There are regular Day &amp; Night Deluxe Bus services from Guwahati to Tinsukia. All modes of road transportations are available to reach Tinsukia. Buses and private vehicles are easily available to reach here.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- The network of transport inside the city is also good. There are local buses Taxis, auto rickshaws and cycle rickshaws available in Tinsukia.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - TINSUKIA - {FAMOUS FOR LASOR TENGA IS A DISH MADE FROM FISH &nbsp;ROHU, TOLATOES, SPINACH AND LEMON ; PITHAS IS A TYPE OF CAKE MADE FROM RICE FLOUR, SUGAR, SALT, COCONUT AND &lsquo;TIL&rsquo;}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - GITANJALI, LOCATED ON AT ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR DAL FRY AND CHICKEN FRY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - BLACK FOREST DE CAFE, LOCATED IN TINSUKIA - (FAMOUS FOR COFFEE AND CAKE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - MADHUBAN SWEET&#39;S, LOCATED ON AT ROAD, TINIKUNIA PUKHURI, NEAR KALI LANDIR - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - GOPALA SWEETS, LOCATED IN TINSUKIA - (FAMOUS FOR RASSGULA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - JAI SANTOSHI MAA HOTEL, LOCATED AT BANK ROAD, CHIRAPATTY - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA AND JALEBI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - PORKBELLY, LOCATED AT GNB ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR PORK MOMOS)&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(358, 14, 31, 1660, 'Arunachal Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'TIRAP (KHONSA)', 'canola-fields-1911392_640.jpg', 'canola-fields-1911392_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Khonsa is the headquarters of Tirap district in Arunachal Pradesh and is located in the Tirap Valley surrounded by Himalayan ranges. Streams, deep gorges, dense forests and snow clad hills are some of the features which describe the terrain in Khonsa. At an average elevation of about 1215 mts from sea level, Khonsa is a beautiful little hill station with natural beauty all around it. Bordering Myanmar in the east and Assam in the south, Khonsa is also an important military area in the Northeast. Khonsa&#39;s beauty lies in most of the natural surroundings; however, one could also enjoy a visit to the Khonsa museum to have a glance at the traditional tribal artefacts. Kheti and Lajo Village, located nearby are some of the tribal villages which one should visit to get a glimpse of the lives and cultures of tribal people. Being on the eastern most tip of India, Khonsa, the beautiful hill station, receives the first rays of the sun in the morning in this part of the world. Not only does sun showers its first rays on the land, various forms of nature too seem to enjoy being present in Khonsa. Apart from the tribes to whom the place is native, Khonsa has warmly embraced people from neighbouring states and hence it has a diverse culture.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Khonsa does not have large number of hotels. So, there are chances that visitors might end up with hotels with basic facilities, but one can easily find Budget hotels here.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Flight</strong> - Closest airport is Dibrugarh which is approximately 100 kms from Khonsa. One can hire a taxi from the airport to reach Khonsa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Road</strong> - Khonsa is well connected to all the neighbouring town and the roads here are in a good condition. There are private and APRTC bus services available. Though the services are not very frequent but it connects to Guwahati and other major cities of Assam.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Train</strong> - There are two options for the railway station. One is Dibrugarh 100 kms away from Khonsa and is connected to some of the major cities of the country. While the better option is Digboi railway station which is closer than Dibrugarh station.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Roads in Khonsa are well connected and jeeps and taxis are the main modes of commuting.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(359, 14, 31, 1656, 'Nagaland', 'INDIA', 'TUENSANG', 'nature-690164_1280.jpg', 'landscape-2089579_1280.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Tuensang is the district headquarters of the largest and eastern district of Nagaland by the same name. It is an important district not only because of its size, but also due to its special constitutional privileges. The city of Tuensang was founded in 1947 for administrating the erstwhile NEFA. The district borders Myanmar on the east and other districts of Nagaland on its other sides. While it was the administrative headquarters for NEFA, Tuensang comprised of the present day Mon, Kiphire and Longleng districts. Together these four districts were also known as Eastern Nagaland. Till 1957, Tuensang was not part of the Indian Territory as well as Myanmar, but when the Kohima and Mokokchung districts of undivided Assam were merged with Tuensang, it was formally recognised as a part of the Indian Territory. During those times, Tuensang was the administrative headquarters of the Naga Hills Tuensang Area. Later in 1963, the state of Nagaland was formed with the three districts of Tuensang, Mokokchung and Kohima. As more districts were formed in Nagaland, the size of Tuensang as a district started diminishing.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are not a lot of options in terms of accommodation in Tuensang. The only options that one would find are the Tuensang Tourist Lodge and the Circuit House that are set by the Government. If the lodging is not available there, one might have to stay with the local families. Don&#39;t worry though, the people here are very hospitable.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\n<strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport to Tuensang is at Dimapur. From Dimapur, other modes of transportation can easily be availed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail</strong> - The Amguri Railway Station is the nearest railway station to Tuensang located at a distance of 65 kilometres. Mariani railway station is also close by.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - The National Highway 155 connects Tuensang to Dimapur and is the lifeline of the town. Taxis, buses all reach Tuensang via this national highway.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Intra city commuting is very comfortable. Good roads and a fairly good amount of availability of cabs ensure that one does not have issues in intra city commuting. Though travelling becomes a major issue during the monsoons.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center">1 - Tuensang - (famous for Maasor Tenga, Aloo Pitika, Khar, Dal and a variety of Chutneys and Pickles)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(360, 14, 31, 733, 'Assam', 'INDIA', 'UDALGURI', 'mountains-1643627_640.jpg', 'mountains-1643627_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The name of the district is derived from its headquarters, Udalguri. The name of Udalguri, according to legend, owes its origin to the fact that there were large numbers of &ldquo;Odal&rdquo; trees in this region. Udalguri district, with an area of 1852 sq kms was formed on June 14th 2004 as one of the four districts under the Bodoland Territorial Council. This district was carved out by bifurcating Darrang district. Udalguri town is the largest town in the district, with an area of 4.69 sq kms. This district is home to Rajiv Gandhi Orang National Park, the oldest game reserve in Assam, Bornadi Wildlife Sanctuary and Bhairabkunda. Udalguri district is one of the 27 districts of Assam state in north&not;eastern India. Udalguri town is the headquarters of the district. This district is bounded by Bhutan and West Kameng district of Arunachal Pradesh state in the north, Sonitpur district in the east, Darrang district in the south and Baksa district in the west.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">In the heart of Udalguri city, within a kilometre radius of the Railway Station are several midsized and budget hotels which offer basic and comfortable amenities. Tourists can practically walk across to the hotels from the Railway Station. Tourists could also stay at the tourist lodges which are operated by the Government.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Golma Bus Stand, Udalguri town. Udalguri is connected with Guwahati and Tezpur by National Highway 52. From the district headquarter it takes 140 kms to reach Guwahati via Darrang and Kamrup districts.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - Udalguri Railway Station is just heart of the Udalguri town. From this station two ways are bifurcated one is towards Upper Assam upto Jonai Station in Dhemaji District and the other one is towards Lower Assam up to Rangia Junction in Kamrup District.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Air</strong> - There are two ways one is Lokapriya Gopinath Bordoloi Airport, Borjhar, Guwahati which is about 140 kms from district headquarter and the other is Saloni Airport, Tezpur which is about 100 kms from District headquarter.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - HOT SNACKS, LOCATED AT TOWN LOOP ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR CHOWMIEN, LOLOS AND CHICKEN ROLL)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - NEZZAS RESTRO, LOCATED AT TANGLA-UDALGURI ROAD, HARISINGA - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;CHINEES DISHES)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(361, 14, 31, 1655, 'Jammu & Kashmir', 'INDIA', 'UDHAMPUR', 'indian-railway-271020_640.jpg', 'indian-railway-271020_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Udhampur is a beautiful district located on the banks of four major rivers namely, Chenab, Ans, Tawi and Ujh, in the south eastern part of Jammu &amp; Kashmir. Udhampur is situated at an altitude ranging between 600 metres to 3000 metres. Udhampur is surrounded by Rajouri District in the west, Anantnag District in the north, Doda and Kathua districts in the northeast and southwest respectively. Apart from being a municipal council, the district is also a Northern Command headquarters of the Indian Army. The destination has been named after the eldest son of Maharaja Gulab Singh, Raja Udham Singh. Maharaja Gulab Singh was the founder of Dogra rule in Jammu and Kashmir. It is believed that the destination has been carved out from the dense forest where Raja Udham Singh frequently visited for hunting trips. The major part of the population includes Hindus and Dogras. Udhampur is also home to various nomadic Gujjars and Bakarwals. People here speak many languages including Hindi, Urdu, Kashmiri and Dogri. Pehari and Goujri are other prominent languages spoken in the district at a large scale. The folk art of the destination can be seen in the local dance and music like heren and fumenie and kud and karak, bhar, bhakh and gwatri. The prime attraction of the destination is Shri Mata Vaishno Devi Shrine, which is situated at a height of 5300 feet on Trikuta Hills of Shivalik Range. Katra is situated at a distance of about 35 kms from Udhampur and serves as the base camp to reach the Sacred Sanctum of Shri Mata Vaishno Devi. The best time to explore Udhampur is during the months of March to October, when the climatic conditions are favourable for sightseeing.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Hotels and Guest houses are established around the city to offer comfortable accommodation facility in Udhampur. They are infused with leisure facilities and amenities crafted with beautiful decor and outstanding features to give pleasurable stay here. Few of the ravishing hotels are incepted on NH 1 in Udhampur that are comprised with high quality services. Recreational resorts are also good option to stay in this city to enjoy the bounty of nature. They offer food restaurants, luxury rooms, and warm reception to every traveller coming to their city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air</strong> - Please remember that there is no direct flights to Udhampur as there is no airport but the nearest airport are Srinagar airport and Jammu airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Rail</strong> - You can easily reach there by train as the Udhampur has its own railway station, you can easily found frequent trains from Delhi to Udhampur which is one of the most convenient mode for the people that are coming there from there.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Road </strong>- Tourists can easily reach there by hiring cabs from Punjab, Himachal Pradesh and Jammu too. Tourists can easily reach Udhampur with the help of buses which is one of the stress free modes; one can easily find buses that are easily accessible from all the cities of Jammu and Kashmir, Himachal Pradesh as well.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(362, 14, 31, 1659, 'Manipur', 'INDIA', 'UKHRUL', 'dawn-190055_1280.jpg', 'dawn-190055_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\nUkhrul, the highest hill station of the state is located at a distance of 83 kms to the east of Imphal. Ukhrul is well developed and is a centre of a colourful warrior tribe, the Tangkhul Nagas. Siroi Hills and Khangkhui Lime Caves are interesting places for excursions. Tangkhul is one of the oldest and major tribes of Manipur. Ukhrul is a beautiful unexplored town in the Ukhrul district of Manipur. The town is made of scenic mountains and hills with a number of tribes inhabiting here who conserve the rich tradition and culture of the region. The town is an ideal destination to spend a relaxed and peaceful time away from all commercial stress. Life here is very slow, calm and peaceful. The beauty of the town is of the Hills and Mountains that stretch as far as eye can see, lush greenery, cool breeze, trees and plants all over the town thus calling it a Green Town. Trade is not very developed here due to its bad connectivity with the commercial cities, hilly area and tribal inhabitant. The commonly done trade is sale of bamboo, timber, cane, honey, horns and agricultural products with the help of the trade societies and in the local market. Most of the commodities and amenities are brought from Imphal and this makes them very expensive.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Ukhrul has budget hotels and lodges that have accommodation. Visitors can also choose to stay in Imphal 85 kms away and come to Ukhrul for a day trip.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Ukhrul is served by the Imphal Airport as it doesn&rsquo;t have any air head of its own. Imphal is located 90 kilometres from Ukhrul and can be travelled on road.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail</strong> - Since Manipur as a state doesn&rsquo;t have any railhead apart from a narrow gauge, the nearest railway station to Ukhrul is in Dimapur, located 210 kilometres away.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Travelling directly from Imphal to Ukhrul is the best way to reach the city on roads. There are bus services available from other parts of Manipur to reach Ukhrul too but travelling from the capital city is the better option. Ukhrul is connected via National Highway 150 which connects the city with Kohima via Jessami.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - Ukhrul - (famous for Morok metpa &nbsp;is a coarse-paste prepared with green or dry red chilies, Ok thongba is pork curry with mustard leaves, Chamthong is a stew &nbsp;made with onions,maroi, ginger and salt, topped with ngari, fried fish pieces)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(363, 14, 31, 1652, 'Himachal Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'UNA', 'una-una-1884940_640.jpg', 'una-una-1884940_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Una is one of the prominent districts and a popular tourist destination, located on the banks of the Swan River in Himachal Pradesh. The district headquarters of Una, the place is famous for numerous tourist hotspots. According to locals, the name &#39;Una&#39; was given by Shri Guru Arjan Dev, the fifth Guru of Sikhs. Etymologically, the word &#39;Una&#39; in Hindi language means &#39;Unaati&#39; or progress. The district of Una was carved out of the Hoshiarpur District of Punjab in 1972. The town of Una is known for its religious sites such as the Gurudwara of Dera Baba Bharbhag Singh, the Bagana Lathian Piplu, and the Chintpurni Temple. The Gurudwara Dera Baba Bharbhag Singh is quite popular among the Sikh Community. Tourists planning a trip to Una are advised to explore the destination during the summer season, which starts from the month of March and lasts till May. During this time, the climate of the region remains pleasant and comfortable.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Where to stay in Una is not a problem at all. Una has many accommodation options for places to stay as there are several private hotels and tourist lodges in this region.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The airport located at Jalandhar is the nearest air base to Una, which is 78 kms away. However, Sri Guru Ram Das Jee International Airport, Amritsar is the nearest major airport to Una.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail</strong> - There is a small railway station located in the town of Una, which connects with major Indian destinations including Delhi, Chandigarh, and Hoshiarpur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Travellers planning a trip to Una can reach the destination by bus services. Luxurious and comfortable buses are available to Una from major cities like Delhi, Panipat, Ambala, Chandigarh, and Ropar. Moreover, visitors can also take buses to Una from nearby destinations such as Hoshiarpur, Jalandhar, and Amritsar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - There are plenty of local buses in Una. Besides this, shared taxis are available. Auto rickshaws also ply in Una.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - VIRSA, UNA, LOCATED AT GREEN AVENUE - (FAMOUS FOR RAJMA RICE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - DAYAL SWEETS, LOCATED AT OPP BUS STAND, HAMIRPUR ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR CHANNE BTHURA AND OTHER SWEETS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - SAINI SWEET SHOP, LOCATED AT SH 25, PROFESSOR COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA AND RAS MALAI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - SWEET SHOP, GHALUWAL, LOCATED IN UNA - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;LASSI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(364, 14, 31, 1660, 'Arunachal Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'UPPER SIANG (YINGKIONG)', 'sunset-317644_640.jpg', 'sunset-317644_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Yingkiong is the headquarter of the Upper Siang district which gets its name from River Siang that flows besides this district. This region is known for its diverse and colourful ethnicity where people live with love and celebrate festivals with zeal. Ponung, Roja and Broh are some of the famous dance forms of the region which has been inhabited mainly by four tribes, Adi, Khamba, Mishmis and Memba. Adventure lovers come here to indulge in hiking, trekking, mountaineering, angling, fishing, rafting, camping and everything else that enlivens their soul. Besides the culture, and a lively atmosphere, the place is known for its spectacular panorama, where there are dense forests and millions of birds with vibrant feathers chirping the excellent melodies and mumbling of rivers flowing here and there.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Sufficient number of options is available for hotels in Yingkiong, tariffs ranging from approximately Rs 200 to Rs 2500. Tourists can also find some rooms and hotels specially designed for senior citizens, kids, honeymoon couples etc. One can also opt to stay at circuit houses known as inspection bungalows which are located on the Pasighat Jeggning Yingkiong trek route.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Flight</strong> - There an airport at Dibrugarh at a distance of approximately 329 kms and this airport is well connected to Delhi, Kolkata and Guwahati. Another option is Lilabari airport 320 kms approximately. Both these airports are located in Assam.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Road</strong> - Yingkiong can be easily reached by boarding a bus from anywhere in Arunachal Pradesh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Train</strong> - Closest railway station is Murkonselek which is at a distance of 220 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Hire a cab to visit Yingkiong since there are not many public transport options available inside.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(365, 14, 31, 743, 'Kerala', 'INDIA', 'ALAPPUZHA (ALLEPPEY)', 'backwater-1644507_1280.jpg', 'backwater-1644507_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Blessed with a wide number of waterways, lagoons, lakes and canals Alleppey is an aquatic paradise within the folds of Gods own country and is aptly called &quot;Venice of the East&quot;. This lively town was founded by the Divan of Travanacore, Raja Keshawadasan. While sailing on houseboats in Alleppey, one can witness the charm of this immaculate backwater town with its plentiful coconut palm lined canals and small hamlets. A long time ago, Alleppey was one of the busiest centres of trade and commerce and was among the more important ports along the Malabar Coast. In search of profits and black gold, traders came here from different parts of the world. Even in its present avtaar, this port is still popular as the hub of prawn farming. For honeymooners it the ideal place to spend a wonderfully romantic time. It is a beautiful location with abundance of flora and fauna and presence of numerous religious as well as historic places and so much more to capture the imagination make Alleppey one of the most attractive places in south India. A trip to Alleppey dictates to take some time off exclusively for appreciating the backwaters and the scenic beauty surrounding it. Beaches, lakes and the much acclaimed cruise in the houseboat are an addition.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">In one of the boat houses that offer a power packed combo of exclusive accommodation and food. The plush little once upon a time royal quarters come equipped with a sleeping area, western style toilets, dining area and a lounge on the deck. Available in varying sizes to suit visitors; these floating cottages are slow moving, easy motorised vehicles fit with generators. Just make sure to get the bookings done well in advance. Otherwise, Alleppey is very tourist friendly and there is no dearth of exclusive or budget hotels, cottages or home stays in and around Alleppey.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - Cochin International Airport is the nearest airport to Alapuzha, which is about 50 kms away. &nbsp;All international, domestic and chartered flights are available here.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail</strong> - Alappuzha has a major rail line that is managed by the Southern Railway. It connects to all cities in North and South India such as Trivandrum, Cochin, Chennai, Bokaro and Mumbai.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - National Highway passes through Alappuzha and connects the city to Ernakulam, Thrissur, Kollam, Kochi and Trivandrum.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Bus Route</strong> - Alappuzha has a big bus stand that connects the city to nearby cities such as Munnar, Madurai, Palakkad, Ernakulum, Mysore etc. Plenty of private and KSRTC buses are available to and fro from the city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Water</strong> - The interesting local ferries are operated by the Kerala Water Transport Department from Alappuzha to different nearby islands through the backwaters both up and down.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Travelling within Alleppey is not a problem as there is abundant number of local buses, auto rickshaws and taxis. Boats and ferry services are the best way to travel places such as Kuttanad, inaccessible by road. Many of Alleppey&#39;s attractions are easily accessible by foot.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - ALAPPUZHA(ALLEPPEY) - {FAMOUS FOR AVIAL IS A DISH MADE FROM MIXTURE OF VEGETABLES AND COCONUT, SEASONED WITH COCONUT OIL AND CURRY LEAVES ; THORAN IS A DISH MADE FROM VEGETABLES LIKE(CABBAGE, YARDLONG BEAN AND OTHER BEAN,UNRIPE JACKFRUIT, BITTERGOURD) AND MIXED WITH GRATED COCONUT, MUSTARD SEEDS, CURRY LEAVES AND TURMERIC POWDER ; OLAN IS A DISH MADE FROM WHITE GOURD, ASH-GOURD OR BLACK-EYED PEAS, COCONUT MILK AND GINGER SEASONED WITH COCONUT OIL ; THALASSERY BIRIYANI IS MADE FROM KAIMA/JEERAKASALA RICE, CHICKEN, SPICES}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - HALAIS RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT NEAR SOUTH POLICE STATION, CCSB ROAD, KODIVEEDU, ALAPPUZHA - (FAMOUS FOR BIRIYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - THAFF RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT VCNB ROAD, KIDANGAMPARAMP, THONDANKULANGARA, THATHAMPALLY - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN CURRY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - MUSHROOM, LOCATED AT CCSB ROAD, KODIVEEDU - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;RUMALI ROTI(CHAPPATI) WITH PANEER BUTTER MASALA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - DAIVAM HOTEL, LOCATED AT NH 47, PATTUKALAM, NEAR PALM FIBRE - (FAMOUS FOR FISH CURRY AND FISH FRY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - GOKULAM RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT CULLEN ROAD, EREZHA, MULLAKKAL - (FAMOUS FOR IDILY AND VADA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - CAFE CATAMARAN, LOCATED AT PADINJARE KURISADI, KANJIRAMCHIRA - (FAMOUS FOR PASTA AND OMELETTE)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(366, 14, 31, 743, 'Kerala', 'INDIA', 'IDUKKI', 'tea-garden-1751083_640.jpg', 'tea-garden-1751083_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Idukki is an alluring retreat for tourists in God&rsquo;s Own Country. Clad in dense green forest and crowned with verdant mountains, it boasts of Anamudi, the highest peak in India. Besides, it also takes pride in being the abode of the second largest arch dam in the world. Being a part of Chera Dynasty and being the home of many early European settlers, Idukki has grabbed a place in the history. It has been an important business hub for many ages as teak, rosewood, sandalwood, ivory and peacock etc are said to be exported from here to many far off countries. Idukki bears testimony of a stone-age civilization, though many historians believe Paleolithic men inhabited here. Remnants of Menhir and Tombs belonging to Stone Age were excavated in 1947-48 near Udumbanchola and Peermede. Contrived as a district on 26 January 1972, the district of Idukki, second largest in Kerala, comprises of many important towns such as Devikulam, Adimali, Udumbanchola, Thekkady, Murrikkaddy, Peermede and Thodapuzha. Idukki also bears rivers such as Thodupuzhayar, Periyar and Thalaya. It also beds thirteen peaks, other than Anamudi that have an altitude of above 2000 mts. Idukki can be called the Power House of Kerala as it caters to 66% of the state&rsquo;s Hydroelectric Power consumption. The Idukki Arch Dam, Kulamavu Dam and Cheruthoni Dam are the three important dams in Idukki. A visit to these dams is worthwhile as they are located in scenic backdrops. Moreover, a wind energy farm is found in Ramakkalmedu, an important hill station and a tourist hotspot of Idukki. An important irrigation project of Kerala the Malankara Reservoir is a visitors&rsquo; favourite place for boating and fishing. Idukki has many attractions in store for its visitors. Apart from the beautiful landscape, it contains numerous tea gardens and coffee plantations, serene springs and enchanting waterfalls and a handful of animal reserves and sanctuaries. The aroma of tea and coffee lingers in the air of Murrikkaddy, a well known plantation in Idukki. Nedumkandam Hill is the land of spice as pepper and cardamom are cultivated here. The cascades of Cellar Kovil gesture a nod of welcome to visitors.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">This place is a tourist destination which caters to lots of travellers throughout the year. Hotels are the best accommodation where tourists can stay comfortably. Tourists can get vast range of hotels from luxury to budget. There are some of the comfortable hotels which offer best facilities to their guests. Tourists can choose the best hotel according to your budget and need.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest airport to Idukki is the Nedumbasseri or Kochi International Airport. It is 160 kms away from Idukki.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The nearest railway station is at Kottayam which is 114 kms from Idukki. Bus services are available from Kottayam to reach Idukki.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Idukki is connected by 6 state highways that pass through it. It also lies on NH 49. It can be reached through KSRTC bus services as well as cab services. Private and luxury bus services makes travelling by road a happy experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- There are numerous coach services that overtake through the town of Idukki. These furthermore serve as an excellent mode of connection from issue of the village to another. They are bargain and frequent and can be availed of from the Idukki coach Terminus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- It is advisable to hire a cab or a car rental if you do not know the language. Otherwise, driving or buses are some of the best ways to cover the region.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - BOMBAY CHAT CENTER, LOCATED IN &nbsp;IDUKKI - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA CHAT AND BHEL PURI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - ZEVIYA RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT &nbsp;MOOLAKADAI, MUNNAR - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;BEEF ROAST AND MUTTON BIRYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - SURYA SOMA, LOCATED AT UDUMALPET RD, NULLATANNI, MUNNA - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN FRIED RICE)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(367, 14, 31, 743, 'Kerala', 'INDIA', 'KANNUR', 'kali-river-453415_1280.jpg', 'kali-river-453415_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kannur, more popularly known as Cannanore, is a northern district in Kerala famed for its vibrant culture and rich heritage. Sharing its borders with the Western Ghats and Arabian Sea, the region exhibits abundant natural beauty and cultural traditions. During ancient times, this district was a cultural, religious as well as a commercial hub of Malabar region. Kannur owes its pulsating culture to several empires that vied to make this territory an abode of their power. The history of the place dates back to the biblical times as the ships of King Solomon are believed to have been anchored on the shores of Kannur. The long trail of invasions by the Dutch, the Portuguese, the Mysore sultanate and the British shaped the history of the region in phenomenal degrees. The name of Kannur has marked in the modem history of Kerala for its vast array of heritage buildings and its most enticing culinary culture. Often referred to as the land of lures and looms, Kannur has gathered worldwide attention with its unique fabric industry and temple folklore forms such as Theyyattam. The proximity of coastal belts confers a pleasant climate to the region enabling travellers to visit the place almost around the year. With its outstanding sightseeing options and trail of the rich heritage, Kannur invites the travellers to experience and explore the wonders hidden within.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The town of Kannur offers several options when it comes to the accommodation. From deluxe and highly luxurious hotels and beach resorts to mid range and budget hotels, the town owns a booming hotel sector. One can also opt for beach facing home stays. There are small houseboats in the backwaters of Kannur where one can get accommodation for a memorable stay in a house boat.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport to reach kannur is Cochin airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Kannur is effortlessly accessible by rail as it houses the Kannur Railway position, an important halt of the south Railways and is well attached to foremost towns of India, especially Kerala. Kannur Junction is a head railway position in the state, from where some trains cross frequently.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Buses are well connected to most of the places of Kerala. All tourists need to do is to take bus from any part of Kerala.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Kannur can be come to road also from many cities and villages of Kerala, and from other parts of the homeland. Motor coaches are readily available from a large number of towns in Kerala.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Kannur is a town that offers many options of commutating from one place to another. Besides walking, tourists may take a bus which is quite cheap. Auto rickshaw is another way of transportation that is regarded as cheap as well as efficient. One can also hire a cab which is best for the tourist visiting for few days. The town also houses many rental car companies where tourists can rent a car for self drive.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SHREE DURGA SWEETS, LOCATED AT KANNUR RD, NEAR HEAD POST OFFICE, MANANCHIRA, KOZHIKODE - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSAS AND &nbsp;KACHORIS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - TAJ KANNUR, LOCATED AT SN PARK ROAD, KANNUR - (FAMOUS FOR DOSA, SAMBHAR AND VEG CUTLET)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - ALI&#39;S FOOD COURT, LOCATED AT PUZHATHI HOUSING COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR GRILLED CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - PREMA CAFE, LOCATED AT MA ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR VEGETABLE BIRIYANI)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(368, 14, 31, 743, 'Kerala', 'INDIA', 'KASARAGOD', 'kerala-618527_6406.jpg', 'kerala-618527_6407.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kasaragod lies on the North Western coast of the Kerala state. There are diverse views on the origin of the name &quot;Kasargod&quot;. It is one of the famous towns and a municipality in Kasaragod district in Kerala. This land is well known as the landmark of various destinations which include Madhur Temple, Mallikkarjuna Temple, Ananthapura temple Theruvatthu Mosque, Chandragiri Fort, Malik Deenar Mosque and Central Plantation Crops Research Institute. In the town, there are 12 rivers and the longest is Chandragiri originating from Pattimala in Coorg. It also embraces the sea at Thalangara which is located near Kasaragod. This beautiful city offers diverse outlines of arts that speak volumes about the wide cultural inheritance of the region. This place is considered as a land of diverse languages. Tulu, Kannada, Malayalam, Konkani and Tamil are some popular languages of the region. There are numbers of Mosques, Temples and Churches which signify communal harmony. It is best to refer to Kasaragod travel guide before planning a trip. Kasargode, the northernmost district of Kerala is of historical and archaeological interest to many. It is said that the Arabs came through Kasargode to Kerala in the AD 9th and 14th centuries. The Bekal fort is the most treasured monument in Kasargode as it runs directly into the sea with bay towards the south.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kasaragod is a beautiful beach town where the stay can become all the more enjoyable with plethora of good accommodation to opt from. The town offers a variety of hotels from highly luxurious to mid range and budget hotels, available at reasonable prices. The town also owns a government owned PWD Rest House offering a comfortable stay.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Flight</strong> - Mangalore, located 65 kms away serves as a nearest airport to Kasaragod town while Kozhkode at a distance of 200 kms is the nearest international airport.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - With a well maintained network of road and a National Highway 66 passing through the town, Kasargod is easily approachable from all nearby cities. In fact several intercity and intra city bus service private as well as KSRTC owned buses plies there.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Kasargod owns a railway station of its own which helps connects the town to many major cities of the country including Goa, Jaipur, Surat, Mangalore, Chennai etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water </strong>- The city of Kasargod is also connected via sea route through Kasargod Port.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Kasargod is city which offers many modes of commutation for its visitors. Taking a bus is the cheapest way to travel through the city while auto rickshaws are also a good mode of transportation. One can also rent a private vehicle. However, for a tourist taxi is one of the best options available in the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - VICEROY RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT CITY TOWER HOTEL, M.G.ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR BIRIYANI, EGG CURRY, EGG FRIED RICE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - VASANTH VIHAR, LOCATED IN KASARAGOD - (FAMOUS FOR DAHI(CURD) VADA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - KOZHIKODEN, LOCATED AT KARANDAKKAD CIRCLE, PADAPALLI PANVEL HIGHWAY, KARANDAKKAD, CHOORI - (FAMOUS FOR BANANA CHIPS)</strong></p>\r\n', '');
