(369, 14, 31, 743, 'Kerala', 'INDIA', 'KOLLAM', 'boat-race-1157518_640.jpg', 'b85.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kollam, best known by its anglicized name Quilon, is a city famed for its commerce and culture. As a coastal city lying on the shores of Ashtamudi Lake and as the headquarters of Kollam district, it contributed massively to the culture and economy of Kerala in myriad ways. History has evidences for the large trade network Kollam had in ancient times with China, Rome and the Middle East. The city had internal commercial links with other parts of India and later became one of the earliest industrial centres. Today Kollam is globally known as the largest producer and exporter of premium quality cashew nuts and is locally referred to as the City of Cashews. The thriving coir manufacturing industry has given the city a facelift as one of the major hub of cottage industries. Steeped in rich past, entangled with unique culture and attributed with nature divine, Kolam lies on the southwest coast of India and has many more hidden treasures troves to be explored. It is one of the oldest ports in Arabian Sea bustling with the activities since the time of ancient Rome. Where the main town is buzzing with activities and hectic, the surroundings compliments it with just the chattering of waves, swaying of coconut palms, calm and green cashew plantations and rustic image of traditional villages. Perfect weather, delicious food and enchanting views of the town never fail to lure tourists from all around the globe.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kollam offers its visitors a wide range of accommodation as per their budget. It houses hotels of all the ranges from moderate and budget to highly luxurious resorts offers best of all the facilities and a comfortable stay.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Kollam is also attached through a well laid out network of streets making it usable from any place in Kerala.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong>&nbsp;- Established at an expanse of 70 kilometres is the Trivandrum aerodrome, which is the closest aerodrome from where Kollam can be reached.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - You can easily reach Kollam by buses as it is well connected to all over Kerala state.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Kollam is a significant railway position and is attached to the rest of Kerala and India through a broad network of railways.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- From buses and auto rickshaws to taxis and private vehicles, Kollam offers all modes of transportation for its visitors. Where buses are the cheapest mode to commute, taxi offers to be the most convenient way of moving in and around the city. One also has an option to hire private vehicle for self drive which is as per the convenience of the tourists.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - ANNS BAKERY &amp; CONFECTIONERY, LOCATED AT OPPOSITE TO BHARAT PETROLEUM, KOTTAYAM-KUMILY ROAD, KANJIKUZHI - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN ROLL)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - BAKEHOUSE, LOCATED AT MANGARAKKALUMKU, PALA ROAD, ETTUMANOOR - (FAMOUS FOR FRUITJUICES AND CAKES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - LEKSHMI BAKERS, LOCATED AT &nbsp;SALEM - KOCHI HWY, KARBALA - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;CHOCOLATE AND PASTRIES)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - RAMEES, LOCATED AT GROUND FLOOR, TV PLAZA, NEAR LIC BUILDING - (FAMOUS FOR BUTTER CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - RED BUBBLE CAFE, LOCATED AT OPP SREE NARAYANA WOMEN&#39;S COLLEGE, JAWAHAR NAGAR, KARBALA - (FAMOUS FOR ROLLS, PUFFS AND CAKES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - MAHALEKSHMI RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT VIDYA NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR FISH FRY AND THE PRAWN FRY)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(370, 14, 31, 1661, 'Telangana', 'INDIA', 'ADILABAD', 'nature-1839942_640.jpg', 'nature-1839942_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Adilabad is a municipal town that lies within the Adilabad district and the town is also the headquarters for the district. Adilabad district is part of the south Indian state of Telengana. According to local legends, the place takes its name from that of Mohamed Adil Shah who was the quondam ruler of Bijapur. Adilabad has a colorful history considering that it was the place of convergence for many cultures and religions. The region also enjoys the distinction of having been ruled by many north Indian dynasties that include the Mauryas, Bhonsle Rajas of Nagpur and the Mughals. Adilabad was also part of the south Indian rulers belonging to dynasties of Satavahanas, Vakatakas, Rashrakutas, Kakatiyas, Chalukyas and Imad Shahis of Berar. The reason behind this is the geographical location of the town. It lies on the border of both central and southern India which made the region vulnerable to attacks and invasions from both sides. As a result, the modern history of Adilabad is an interesting amalgamation of the Marathi and Telugu cultures. The local population of Adilabad follows traditions that are a mix of the two cultures, but these traditions have now become an integral part of the daily lives of the people. Also, the Bengali, Rajasthani and Gujarati cultures have found prevalence in the area.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Adilabad is small town that offers many options of mid range and budget accommodations. However, tourists won&rsquo;t find many luxurious hotels in the area. But the stay at the hotel is quite comfortable and food delicious.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Flight</strong> - The nearest airport to Adilabad is Hyderabad as well as Nagpur. Where Nagpur owns a domestic airport which is well connected to all the major cities of India, Hyderabad is an international airport which receives flight from all major cities of India as well as other major countries.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - This town is easily approachable through a well maintained network of roads. National Highway 7 also passes through the town and connects it to various neighbouring cities and states. Regular bus services plies between Adilabad and other neighbouring cities and towns.<br />\r\n<strong>&nbsp;<br />\r\nBy Train </strong>- Adilabad houses a railway station of its own. It is well connected to several major cities via frequent train services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - To explore this beautiful town, taxi is the best way of commuting from one place to another. One can also take bus as well which proves to be a cheap form of transportation and quite convenient as well though a bit slow.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - ADILABAD - [FAMOUS FOR SAJJA ROTI (PENISETUM), UPPUDI PINDI (BROKEN RICE), JONNA ROTTE (SORGHUM), VEPUDU, POTLAKAYA PULUSU, ONKKAYA BRINJAL VEPUDU, ARINTIKAYA BANANA PULUSU, PALAKOORA (SPINACH COOK WITH LENTILS) ; VEG DISHES ARE GONGURA, CHANA DAL, BACHILI KURA (SPINAICH WITH TAMARIND PASTE IN CURRY), PACHI PULUSU (RASAM MADE FROM CHILLIES, TAMARIND AND ONIONS) ; MEAT DISH ARE KODI PULUSU IS CHICKEN CURRY AND MAMASM VEPUDU. OORRU, &nbsp;Golichina Mamsam (Spicy Mutton) ; &nbsp;SNACKS ARE CHAKINALU OR SAKINALU ; &nbsp;SWEET DISH ARE MADUGULU MADE FROM &nbsp;MILK, PHARDA PHENI(A WAFER SWEET) ; POPULAR DISHES ARE JONNA ROTI (FLAT BREAD PREPARED FROM SORGHUM), KODI KURA, GUDDU PULUSU, SAKINALU (IN MAKAR SANKRANTI), UlAVACHARU MAHUA (GULMOHAR)DRINK (IPPA KALLU), Taddy (Kawal DRINK IS BEST)] &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">2 - NIRMAL DHABA, OPPOSITE KANCHA KATTA ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR SAMBHAR ANDRASHAM)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(371, 14, 31, 732, 'Andhra Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'KARIMNAGAR', 'i37.jpg', 'i38.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Karimnagar, popularly known as Kareem Nagar is an antique city resplendent with architectural marvels and cultural heritage of the yore. Located in the state of Telangana it is one of the famous cities of the South Indian state and is located on the banks of Manair River, a tributary of the Godavari River. Karimnagar travel guide is incomplete without a mention of its rich cultural and spiritual legacy. Karimnagar was ruled by different kingdoms over the years and thus the rich cultural influence. The area was first ruled by the Satavahanas, followed by the Vishnukumdin, Vemulavada Chalukyas, Qutub shahis Kakatiyas and Asaf Jahis. It is a major business spot and is rising as a supreme educational hub. A lot of famous personalities have spent time in Karimnagar. Notable among them are P.V. Narasimha Rao, the former Prime Minister of India; Prof G. Ram Reddy, Vemulawada Bheema Kavi. The district is bounded in the north by Adilabad, in the south west by Medak district, in the south by Warangal District and Nizamabad District in the west. Karimnagar is a city located along the Manair River, which is a big tributary running out from the Godavari River in Telangana. This is considered as a popular financial area and is speedily emerging as a major educational hub. Karimnagar has many tourist attractions, some of them being Elgandal Fort, Ujwal Park, Rajeev Dear Park, and many famous pilgrimage sites. Karimnagar has a rich historical background. It used to be a regional capital for Nizam.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Hotels in Karimnagar are not very expensive and accommodation options are available for all types of hotels according to the budget. These include Srinivasa Hotel on Bus Stand Road, Manair Hotel near Karimnagar Urban, Nawab&rsquo;s Hotel on Civil Hospital Road and Urban and City Inn Hotel. Karimnagar has a lot for medium to budget accommodation options with all facilities which make the stay a reliable and memorable one.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Karimnagar doesn&#39;t have its own airport. The closest airport is Rajiv Gandhi International airport at Hyderabad and all flights available from here for rest of the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Karimnagar is well connected to the railway junctions and also have its own railway station connected by a single line.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Karimnagar is well connected to central city Hyderabad so one can easily reach here via personal car or hired taxi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Karimnagar has its own bus stop from where tourists can ply for every major city nearby it.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - NEW PEACOCK RESTAURANT, FIRST FLOOR, ASLAMI COMPLEX, &nbsp;RAJEEV CHOWK - (FAMOUS FOR MUTTON KOFTA BIRYANI, SCHEZWAN CHICKEN SOFT NOODLES, CHICKEN STEAK SIZZLER)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - ANVITHA FAST FOOD, JAGITAL ROAD, OPPOSITE SREE LATHA TOWERS, CHRISTAN COLONY ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR VARITIES OF SNACKS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - GOLI VADA PAV, RAJEEV CHOWK, ASLAMI MASJID- (FAMOUS FOR PANEER ROLL, MIX VEGETABLE VADA PAV, AALO TIKKI VADA PAV)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - GEETHA BHAVAN RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT JYOTHINAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR SNACK LIKE SAKINALU, SARVAPINDI AND SWEET IS &nbsp;MAMAJI JALEBI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n5 - KARIMNAGAR - [FAMOUS FOR NON VEG DISHES - TAWA FISH AND TAWA CHICKEN, CHILLI PRAWNS, BONELESS CHICKEN BIRYANI AND FISH BIRYANI]&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(372, 14, 31, 1661, 'Telangana', 'INDIA', 'KHAMMAM', 'ramparts-285280_6401.jpg', 'ramparts-285280_6402.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Khammam, a city located in the southern Indian state of Telengana is also known as the headquarters for the Khammam District. The city became a municipal corporation recently after the addition of 14 nearby villages within its area. The city is situated about 273 kms on the east from the capital city of Hyderabad and is a favourite destination for travellers coming to Telengana. According a local legend, the place derives its name from the Narsimhadri temple which was initially known as Stamba Sikhari and Stambhadri later on. The temple is dedicated to Lord Narasimha Swamy who is believed to be one of the incarnations of Lord Vishnu. It has been proven that the temple has been in existence since the time of Treta Yuga, almost 1.6 million years ago. The temple is located atop a hill and below the temple is a vertical rock that acts as a pillar. Khammam is a beautiful city situated on the banks of river Munneru, a tributary of river Krishna. The city of Khammam holds an important place in the history of Telengana. The famous Khammam Fort has historical significance not only for the city, but also for the state of Telangana. The fort stands majestically atop a hill and is an example of both valour and a supreme amalgamation of different styles of architecture. Khammam was the hub of commercial and social activities in ancient times, especially during the reign of the Taluks. It has been ruled by many kings and was under the reign of many dynasties, and they have all left their indomitable mark on the history, art and architecture of the region. The city of Khammam is also a fine example of the communal harmony. People of different religions practice their different cultures, and this is what gives Khammam its unique identity.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Khammam is one of the most tourist visited cities in Telangana so numerous hotels are functioning in the city to provide quality stay to its customers. Khammam has ample of hotels ranging decent to moderate hotels. One can find these hotels with generally good hospitable staff and facilities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Flight</strong> - Khammam has no airport, the nearest favoured airport is the Hyderabad Airport.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Khammam has two national highways running through it; as a result this city is well connected by roads. State owned public buses, private vehicles and auto rickshaws frequently commute on this route.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Khammam has well established railway station which lies on rains Vijayawada line. Khammam has regular trains from all over India halting here since it falls on the Hyderabad Vishakhapatnam line.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Local buses are the cheapest mode of transport here. However if time bound, hiring a cab or private vehicle for a day would be more feasible. Tourists can also avail short fare taxis to commute to your planned destinations.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - KHAMMAM - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;VEG DISHES MENTHI CHAMAN WITH NAANS, MIRCHI BAJJI AND JALEBI, HAREES AND HALEEM, SOUTH INDIAN DISHES ARE &nbsp;IDLI, DOSA, VADA, AND PURI}&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - HAVELI RESTAURANT, Wyra Rd, VDO&#39;s Colony - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN BIRYANI, MUTTON AND FISH BIRYANI)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(373, 14, 31, 743, 'Kerala', 'INDIA', 'KOTTAYAM', 'beach-731147_640.jpg', 'beach-731147_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kottayam is an ancient city of Kerala. It is located in Kottayam district, one of the districts of God&rsquo;s Own Land. The city has a big contribution to print media and literature and hence rightfully referred as &ldquo;Akshara Nagari&quot; meaning &ldquo;city of letters&rdquo;. Kottayam got its name from the word &ldquo;Kottaya&rdquo; which is a combination of the Malayalam words &ldquo;kott&rdquo; meaning &ldquo;fort&rdquo; and &ldquo;akam&rdquo; meaning &ldquo;inside&rdquo;; the literal meaning being &ldquo;the interior of a fort&rdquo;. The old town of Kottayam is now called Kunnumpuram and is located on a hilltop. The fort from which the city got its name is Thaliyil Kotta which was founded by the Rajah of Thekkumcoor. A village developed within the walls of the fort and thus the city of Kottaym came into being. The enchanting Western Ghats borders Kottayam on the east and the mesmerising Vembanad Lake lies in the west of Kottayam. It is a magnificent place with breathtaking landscape. Culturally rich and naturally enchanting, Kottayam is a destination in Kerala offering a complete package for a perfect vacation. It is an ancient town located on a hilltop bordered with tantalizing Western Ghats on east and green paddy fields and thrilling Vembanad Lake on the west. Apart from the nature&#39;s bounty, the town has many laurels to its name. It is a proud town to achieve 100 percent literacy in India for the first time.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Accommodation in this beautiful town of Kottayam is quite easy to find. The town is adorned with variety of hotels ranging from budget and mid range to deluxe all the while offering delicious food and a comfortable stay. One can also find quite attractive tour package at the hotels to explore the city. Also tourists can arrange for forest safaris and bird watching sessions before hand.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Cochin International Airport is the nearest airport to Kottayam, which is about 90 kms away. &nbsp;All international, domestic and chartered flights are available here.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail</strong> - Kottayam railway station is situated in the heart of the town and is managed by the Southern Railway. It is a major rail line that connects to all cities in North and South India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Kottayam is well connected by road. National Highway 220 connects Kottayam to Kollam, Theni and Tamil Nadu etc. National Highway 208 connects Kottayam to Madurai. State Highways 1 or Main Central road pass through Kottayam.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Kottayam has a big bus stand that connects the city to nearby cities such as Munnar, Madurai, Mysore, Kochi etc. Plenty of private and KSRTC buses are available to and fro from the city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water</strong> - Kottayam Port is a minor port that uses inland water way and is situated at Nattakom, on the banks of Kothoor river. The Kerala State Water Transport Department operates ferry services through the backwaters in and around Kottayam city. Ferries are a major mode of transport that connects the city to Kumarakom and Alappuzha and other small destinations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Kottayam operates all kinds of transportation services starting with the local bus service. It is the cheapest way of commuting; however remember that buses are quite crowded during the rush hours. Auto rickshaws in the town are also quite inexpensive but make sure to bargain a good deal out of them. Local taxis are however the best option if want to explore in and around the town. Car rental companies are also available in the area if in mood to self drive. But walking is the best and healthy way to explore this small town.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - GREEN LEAF&#39;S RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT MC ROAD, MUPPAIKAD - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN BIRIYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - KANA RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT SH 1, BAKER HILL - (FAMOUS FOR BUTTER CHICKEN)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - AISWARYA RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT AISWARYA BUILDING, SH 1, NATTAKOM - (FAMOUS FOR POROTTA &nbsp;AND FISH CURRY)&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - TRIVANDRUM CHICKEN CORNER, LOCATED AT KUDAKASSERY BUILDING, LOGOS JUNCTION, NEAR LOGOS CENTRE, SHASTRI ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN FRY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - UDAYAM RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT NEAR VARISSERY JUNCTION, MEDICAL COLLEGE BYPASS ROAD, VARISSERY - (FAMOUS FOR MASSALA PURI)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(374, 14, 31, 1661, 'Telangana', 'INDIA', 'MAHABUBNAGAR', 'stairs-338428_6402.jpg', 'stairs-338428_6403.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Mahabubnagar town is located at a distance of 96 kms from Hyderabad city. Formerly called Rukmammapeta and Palamooru, it derived the name of Mahabubnagar in 1890, in the honour of Mir Mahbub Ali Khan Asaf Jah VI, one of the rulers of the Nizam dynasty of Hyderabad. Mahabubnagar&rsquo;s border is marked by River Krishna in the south with Andhra Pradesh. Mahabubnagar is the largest district of Telangana State. It was under the rule of Satavahana Dynasty and then Chalukyan Dynasty in South India between the periods of 5th and 11th century AD. Later it was under the Golconda State and finally Hyderabad State. &nbsp;Krishna and Tungabhadra rivers flow through this district. Dindi River is an important tributary of the river Krishna in this district. Mahabubnagar district is home to famous temples and many religious and heritage sites of historical importance. Jurala Dam, Alamapur&rsquo;s Jogulamba temple and Gadwal fort are some of the key destinations. Kollapur is a famous tourist attraction with architectural sites dating back to 2nd century BC. Koilsagar is a key dam, which attracts tourists. Mallela Theertham is a popular waterfall situated in Nallamala forest region. The district has an important Tiger sanctuary located near the Srisailam forest area.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Alampur is a heritage destination in Mahabubnagar district of Telangana where there are regular tourists that visit the famous Jogulamba temple and the Sangameshwara temple. The hotel located close to Tungabhadra River is maintained well by the tourism department and there are adequate AC and Non AC rooms for catering to the tourists.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Mahabubnagar doesn&#39;t have its own airport but Rajiv Gandhi International Airport of Hyderabad is closest one to this place. This airport well connected to all over the country and flights available time to time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Mahabubnagar has three railway stations named as main station, town station and Yenugonda station. All are well connected to rest of state and Delhi too.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Mahabubnagar is well connected to NH 44 so one can easily via his personal vehicle or hired car.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - As APSRTC is here so bus service is also a feasible way of transport.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - MAHABUBNAGAR - [FAMOUS FOR TALAKAYA KURA, SAJJAAND MAKKA ROTI, UPUDU PINDI, PAASHAM, SABHUDHANA UPMA, MAKKA GUDALU, BOBARLA GUDALLU, MAKKAJONA GARELU, KODI,PULUSU, ROYYALA KURA, KODI GUDLA PULUSU, Boondi AND RAVA LADDU, GAVVALA, RAVVA KESARI, ARISELU, BHAGARA ANNAM, BIRYANI, BONDA, CHAKINALU, CHAPATHI, DOSA, HYDERABADI BIRYANI, IDLI, SARWAPINDI, BAKSHALU, ATTLU, GARELU, JONNA GADAKA, SALLA CHARU, PAPPUCHARU, Golichina Mamsam, Gulab jamun, Madugulu, Pusa, Jonna Gadaka, Salla Charu, Kichidi, Osmania Biscuit, Paya, Pulihora, Sheer khurma]&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - Dial Palamuru Food,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Brms Complex, Signal Above Karnataka Bank, Mettugadda - (FAMOUS FOR FRESH JUICES, PANEER TIKKA, VEG SEEKH KEBAB AND ARITIES OF PARATHAS, MUTTON KOLAPURI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(375, 14, 31, 743, 'Kerala', 'INDIA', 'MALAPPURAM', 'conollys-plot-1360323_640.jpg', 'conollys-plot-1360323_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Malappuram is a northern district in Kerala known for its rich culture, historic significance and remarkable heritage. The region of Malappuram, speckled with small hills and mounds, justifies its name which in Malayalam means &lsquo;Hill Top&rsquo;. With a history that weaves ancient and modern times together, the region contributed extensively to the culture, religion, economy as well as tourism of Kerala. The district invited the attention of economists from all over the country in recent times due to its Gulf migrant population which gave rise to an unprecedented economic boom. Three rivers, namely Chaliyar, Bharathapuzha and Kadalundi, flow through the land of Malappuram enriching both its soil and its culture. The powerful army of the Zamorins kings of Calicut was headquartered here in olden days. The name of the district is marked in the history of Indian nationalism for being the venue for Khilafat Movement and Mopila Revolt. Malappuram is the birth place of the Muslim dance form, Oppana. The small towns of Malappuram contributed to the cultural, political, literary traditions of Kerala in matchless manners. Thirunavaya was a hub for Vedic education during medieval times and from Kottakkal originated traditional medical system of Ayurveda. Ponnani and Nilambur have given global acclamation to Malappuram.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Malappuram have several luxurious, budgeted, AC hotels, non AC hotels and resorts to meet the requirement of every tourist and visitors of this city. These hotels provide best accommodation facilities along with luxury comfort to their visitors. They also provide multi cuisine food, which provide home like feeling to customers. Apart from this, other facilities like gym, parking, recreation room, meeting room, swimming pool, etc are also provided to the customers at hotels in Malappuram.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport is the Kozhikode International Airport at Karippur, 36 kms away from Malappuram.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Railway</strong> - Tirur Railway Station at 28 kms is the nearest railhead and Kozhikode station is 36 kms away.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Bus Services are available to all centres and rural areas in Malappuram and its nearby places. 93 schedules are operated by KSRTC on the main routes besides the 300 long route buses passing through the district of Malappuram.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Malappuram is well connected to all the major towns in Kerala, Karnataka and Tamil Nadu by an excellent road network. NH 17 and NH 213 pass through the district of Malappuram.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Taxis and Buses are easily available.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - MALAPPURAM - {FAMOUS FOR PATHIRIS,WHICH IS A BREAD PREPARED WITH RICE ; &nbsp;PUTTU IS A BREAKFAST DISH MADE FROM RICE FLOUR AND COCONUT ; &nbsp;UNNAKKAYA IS A SNACK FRIED BOILED RIPE BANANA PASTE WHICH IS MADE TO WRAP CASHEWS, RAISINS AND SUGAR ; PATHIRI IS A DISH MADE FROM RICE FLOUR}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - FOOD N JOY FAMILY RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT NH-17,CHANGUVETTY, KANYAKUMARI, PANVEL HIGHWAY - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN AND FISH CURRIES)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - SWEEDISH CAKES,CAFE &amp; RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT MUNDUPARAMBA BYPASS ROAD, KAVUNGAL, UP HILL - (FAMOUS FOR ICE CREAM)&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(376, 14, 31, 1661, 'Telangana', 'INDIA', 'MEDAK', 'india-771288_1280.jpg', 'india-771288_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Medak, a municipal town in the Medak District of the state of Telengana, lies at a distance of about 100 kms from the capital city of Hyderabad. Medak has a very interesting history associated with it. The original name of the town is believed to be Siddapuram which was later changed to Gulshanabad. The town was at the height of progress during the reign of Kakatiya dynasty. In fact, the Kakatiya king Pratapa Rudra got a citadel built around Medak to protect the town from any sort of invasion. The citadel was constructed over a hillock and was named Methukurdurgam. It was also popularly referred to as Methukuseema by the locals. &lsquo;Methuku&rsquo; is a Telugu word that means cooked grains of rice. Medak is very popular among the nearby towns and cities because of the many festivals that are celebrated here with a lot of pomp and show. In fact, all the festivals of Telengana are celebrated in the region, and many people come from far and wide to participate in the festivities. The most famous festival in the town is the festival of Bathukamma and is celebrated on a large scale. The festival belongs to the region of Telangana and is celebrated by only women. The festival is celebrated during the time of Navarathri and is for honouring goddess Gouri. The goddess is worshipped in Telangana in the form of Bathukamma. The word is actually an invocation to the goddess to come alive. Bathukamma paduga is an autumn festival and is celebrated for nine days.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Medak Fort is a heritage structure and a popular tourist attraction of Medak town. The well maintained suites offer maximum comfort to tourists who opt for this hotel for accommodation. The dining facility provided in open area, offers a memorable experience to the tourists staying at Haritha Hotel, Medak. Haritha Accommodation at Medak has rooms which are built close to the walls of the Medak fort, offering a wonderful experience. Haritha Accommodation at Medak offers unparallel ambience amid a wonderful heritage backdrop.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport to Medak is Hyderabad at a distance of about 100 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail </strong>- Kamareddy is the nearest railhead to Medak at a distance of nearly 60 kms.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Bus</strong> - Medak is well connected by States buses from Hyderabad, Sangareddy, Nizamabad, Karimnagar, Warangal, and Siddipet.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - The NH 7 highway from Hyderabad (via Medchal) will take to Medak in less than two hours.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - MEDAK - [FAMOUS FOR TALAKAYA KURA, SAJJAAND MAKKA ROTI, UPUDU PINDI, PAASHAM, SABHUDHANA UPMA, MAKKA GUDALU, BOBARLA GUDALLU, MAKKAJONA GARELU, KODI PULUSU, ROYYALA KURA, KODI GUDLA PULUSU, Boondi AND RAVA LADDU, GAVVALA, RAVVA KESARI, ARISELU, BHAGARA ANNAM, BIRYANI, BONDA, CHAKINALU, CHAPATHI, DOSA, HYDERABADI BIRYANI, IDLI, SARWAPINDI, BAKSHALU, ATTLU, GARELU, JONNA] &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(377, 14, 31, 1661, 'Telangana', 'INDIA', 'NALGONDA', 'hillock-370654_640.jpg', 'hillock-370654_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Nalgonda is a municipal town in the Nalgonda district of the state of Telengana. The name of the town is a combination of two Telugu words; Nalla and Konda that stand for &lsquo;Black&rsquo; and &lsquo;Hill&rsquo; respectively. Nalgonda is a city with deep rooted rich history and equally intriguing cultural heritage. With its roots going back to Paleolithic Age proved by enough evidence excavated from Yeleswaram, Nalgonda also displays the hints of Neolithic culture with further unearthing of sling stones and other such objects. The city derives its name from a combination of two Telugu words &#39;Nalla&#39; and &#39;Konda&#39; meaning &#39;Black Hills&#39;. In fact, today the city of Nalgonda presents a colourful blend of diverse religious cultures and traditions reflecting the beautiful past of the city that was once ruled by several Hindu and Muslim rulers at different points of time. The city is also renowned for its strong political taste which was mainly established under the reign of Mauryas; however it was during the rule of Satavahanas that the trade with Roman Empire commenced. At present this amazing place called Nalgonda is blessed with the footprints left behind by several great kingdoms and dynasties that called this place their home.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Nalgonda is place which offers several options of accommodations, mostly in form of medium and budget hotels. The place also offers few guest houses as per the taste of tourists. Swagat Lodge, Hotel Balaji Grand and Sri Vijayadurga Hotel are few among many.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Flight</strong> - Rajiv Gandhi International Airport at Hyderabad serves as the nearest airbase to the city of Nalgonda. Being an international airport it tends to connect the place with several major cities of the country. The city lies at a distance of nearly 118 kms from airport and can be easily approached by taxi available.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - When it comes to commuting to the city via road, in that case Nalgonda is easily accessible by a well maintained network of roads. Regular buses run by private owners and state plies to and fro from Nalgonda.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Nalgonda houses a railway station of its own located around 3 kms from the city. It is well connected to all the major cities via regular train service.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Bus being the cheapest is also the slowest mode while auto rickshaws are pretty convenient and are always up for some good bargaining. However, as a tourist, taxi might seem the best option as it is fastest of all the modes but a bit expensive too.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - NALGONDA - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;ARISELU, BHAGARA ANNAM, BIRYANI, BONDA, CHAKINALU, CHAPATHI, DOSA, HYDERABADI BIRYANI, IDLI, SARWAPINDI, BAKSHALU, ATTLU, GARELU, JONNA GADAKA, SALLA CHARU, PAPPUCHARU, TOMATO CHUTNEY, GARIJALU, MADUGULU, PUSA, KUDUMULU, UNDRALLU, SEMIYA, BELLAM ANNAM, VADA, PURI, UPMA, CHEPALA PULUSU, KICHIDI, OSMANIA BISCUIT, PAYA, PULIHORA, SHEER KHUMARA, TALAKAYA KURA, SAJJA ROTTE, MAKKA ROTTE, UPUDU PINDI, PAASHAM, SABHUDHANA UPMA, MAKKA GUDALU, BOBARALA GUDALLU, MAKKAJONA GARELU, KODI PULUSU, ROYYALA KURA, KODI GUDLA PULUSU, BOONDI AND RAVA LADDU, GAVVALU, RAVA KESAR]&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(378, 14, 31, 1661, 'Telangana', 'INDIA', 'NIZAMABAD', 'india-995576_6402.jpg', 'india-995576_6403.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Nizamabad, also known as Indhooru and Indhrapuri, is a city as well as a municipal corporation located in the Nizamabad district of the south Indian state of Telengana. Nizamabad district&rsquo;s headquarters are also located in the town of Nizamabad, and the place is the 10th largest town of the state. During the 8th century, the town was under the reign of Indra Vallabha Panthya Vasrha Indra Som who belonged to the Rashtrakuta Dynasty. The place was named Indhrapuri after the king. However, with the construction of a railway line between the cities of Secunderabad and Manmad, a new railway station was added the Nizamabad railway station. Nizamabad enjoyed its golden period during the reign of Nizam-ul-Mulk who ruled the region for long years. He was a great patron of art and architecture and consequently built many religious institutions in the area including mosques and Hindu temples. There are many towns and villages that come under the Nizamabad district including Armuru, Bodhan, Banswada, Kamareddy and many more. Located in the town of Bodhan is the Nizam Sugar Factory that was once known as the biggest such factory in the whole of Asia.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Telangana State Tourism Development Corporation offers luxurious, comfortable and world class accommodation. There are spacious rooms with good water supply and excellent accommodation with a good restaurant operated by the tourism department. The modern ambience and the excellent facilities offered by Telangana Tourism makes the stay of tourists pleasant and memorable. In addition, there are many private resorts and hotels that cater to the tourist flow with quality facilities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Flight</strong> - The nearest airport is in Hyderabad at about 200 kms from Nizamabad.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Hyderabad has the best connectivity to Nizamabad. There are bus services that frequent every 15 minutes from Hyderabad to Nizamabad. The Andhra Pradesh State Tourism Corporation runs premium Mercedes Benz buses from Hyderabad and Bangalore. There are a lot of private Volvo buses plying as well.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The Nizamabad is well connected by rail to all the major cities of South and Central India, namely, Mumbai, Pune, Bhopal, Bangalore, Nagpur and cities in Andhra Pradesh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Nizamabad is well connected to all places and commuting within the city is best done by booking a private cab, although there are private and APSTRC buses.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - NIZAMABAD - [FAMOUS FOR RICE MEAT DISHES, SOUTH INDIAN CUISINE ARE DOSA, VADA, PURI AND IDLY, HYDERABADI BIRYANI, &nbsp;HAREES AND HALEEM, NIZAMABAD KI THARI AND NIZAMABAD KA BHEJA GUTTI VANKAI, NIZAMABAD FRUIT SALAD LASSI MILK SHAKE AND &nbsp;FALUDA]&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(379, 14, 31, 743, 'Kerala', 'INDIA', 'PALAKKAD', 'mother-831702_640.jpg', 'mother-831702_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Palakkad, otherwise known by its anglicized name Palghat, is a district in Kerala that lies along the serpentine mountain ranges of the Western Ghats. What makes Palakkad distinct from other parts of Kerala is its predominantly rural nature coupled with enormous expanses of paddy fields. Endless stretch of palm trees, green carpeted landscapes, dense tropical forests and undulating hilly terrains make Palakkad a visual treat to spectators. By contributing massively to the rice production of Kerala, Palakkad has rightfully grabbed two titles: &lsquo;The Rice Bowl of Kerala&rsquo; and &lsquo;The Granary of Kerala&rsquo;. Palakkad, a town located in the Palakkad district of Kerala lies in a depression in the Western Ghats called the Palgat Gap. It is the place where the state of Kerala is connected to the state of Tamil Nadu. There are many small villages that are located in and around the place and in many of these villages the language spoken is Tamil as opposed to the main language of the state which is Malayalam. These villages are a good place to visit and experience a quintessential Tamil Brahmin life. Some of the villages that are located in the region are, Old Kalpathy, New Kalpathy, Noorani, Thirunellai, Chatapuram, Tharekadu and many others. There are numerous local festivals that are celebrated in the area and the temples are decorated during this period. Some of the festivals are the Padur Vela, Pudduseri Vedi, Tharakad Sivan Koil Siva Rathry and many others.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Palakkad has a number of big and small hotels, guest houses and luxury resorts that have good accommodation. Home stays are also available at a very economical cost. There are a few Ayurvedic Healing Resorts that have good treatments along with luxury accommodation.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Palakkad does not have an airport. The nearest airport is located at Coimbatore which lies at a distance of about 50 kms from the town of Palakkad. Taxi services are available from Coimbatore airport to Palakkad town.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Palakkad Railway Junction also known as Olavakkode Junction is a major railhead in Kerala. It is well connected to all part of Kerala and the major cities of India such as Bangalore, Chennai, Delhi, Mumbai and Hyderabad.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Palakkad town is well connected by road and buses are available from all the neighbouring districts as well as some of the towns in Tamil Nadu. Kerala State Transport buses and private buses run regular services to towns and cities such as Coimbatore, Kochi, Calicut and Thrissur. Luxury and Volvo buses are available to Palakkad from Thiruvananthapuram, Bangalore and Chennai.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Taxis and Buses are easily available. Many places can be covered on foot.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - PALAKKAD - {FAMOUS FOR CHAKKA HALWA (JACKFRUIT HALWA) ; PODUTHUVAL IS A DISH MADE FROM VEGETABLES PREPARED BY USING GRATED COCONUT,GREEN CHILLIES,CUMIN AND TURMERIC COOKED WITH TOOR DAL OR MOONG DAL ; &nbsp;KOOTTU IS A TYPE OF DISH MADE FROM VEGETABLE, LENTILS}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - NOORJAHAN, LOCATED AT SANTHI NAGAR, SULTANPET, GANDHI BAZAAR ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR BIRIYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - NMR BIRIYANI HOUSE, LOCATED AT HARIKKARA STREET, NEAR MADHAVI AMMA NURSING HOME - (&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;FAMOUS FOR BIRIYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - ARIPPA RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT COLLEGE ROAD, NEAR HEAD POST OFFICE - (FAMOUS FOR PUTTU IS A BREAKFAST DISH MADE FROM RICE FLOUR AND COCONUT)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - MANI&#39;S CAFE, LOCATED AT OLAVAKODE - (FAMOUS FOR DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - THE MAGIK OVEN, LOCATED AT STADIUM BYPASS ROAD, SELVAPALAYAM - (FAMOUS FOR BURGER AND PIZZA)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(380, 14, 31, 743, 'Kerala', 'INDIA', 'PATHANAMTHITTA', 'bicycle-path-1666762_640.jpg', 'bicycle-path-1666762_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Pathanamthitta is a large town located in the state of Kerala and is one of the most popular tourist destinations in the state. It is the youngest district of Kerala located in its southern part. The town is a major destination for pilgrims for all over India, as it serves as the gateway to the popular pilgrimage of Sabarimala.Tourists can travel to Pathanamthitta to unwind and let off steam as the town is located in an extremely serene setting, amidst dense forests and enchanting scenery. Pathanamthitta is a very cosmopolitan area, and the place has something for both the young and the old. There are countless places to visit in the town of Pathanamthitta and its surrounding regions, and most of these locations are mainly temples and religious centres. This is one of the reasons why pilgrims and people looking for peace of mind flock to the town of Pathanamthitta. Popular places in Pathanamthitta that tourists should visit during the trip to the town are the Sabarimala Temple, the Sreevallabha Temple, Kodumon Chilanthiyambalam, which is a spider temple, the Malankara Orthodox Church in Parumala and the Siva Temple located in Nilakkal. There are various monuments and places of historical importance in the town of Pathanamthitta that tourists who are history buffs can enthusiastically visit. These include the Kaviyoor Mahadeva Temple, the Paliakkara Church and monument of Adoor Velu Thampi Deva, a freedom fighter.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The holy town of Pathanamthitta offers several options to its tourists when it comes to accommodation. It houses numerous budget hotels. However, there are only few mid range and luxurious places to stay; the reason being that all the pilgrims prefer to stay away from the luxury. Budget hotels are quite easy to find and offers just the basic facilities and amenities to maintain their austere lifestyle.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Cochin International aerodrome is established about 142 kms from the town. Thiruvananthapuram worldwide aerodrome is also established at 113 kms from town which is closest to Pathanamthitta.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- The town does not have its own train station. Thiruvalla railway position is is established about 30 kms from the town and Chengannur trains position is 26 kms away.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - As a foremost pilgrimage destination there are diverse coach services both by KSRTC and personal operators from diverse towns of Kerala as well as from other components of homeland. Frequent motor coaches are accessible from cities like Kottayam, Kochi, Thiruvananthapuram, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Tourists can easily get buses from most of the places, as there is regular bus services, even they can travel on private buses too.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Pathanamthitta is a small town where there is regular influx of tourists and pilgrims in large number. The transportation facilities in the town are plenty and according to everyone&#39;s budget. The place offers a very efficient bus service and is an economical way to commute. Auto rickshaws are also an option especially in case of commuting between the tourist attractions. Taxi is another best option which is available at quite cheap rates. Car rentals are also easily available in the town where tourists can self drive if well versed with the place.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - AANANDA BAVAN VEGETARIAN RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT THIRUVALLA-KUMBAZHA HWY - (FAMOUS FOR MASALADOSA AND CHILLY POROTTA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - GREEN CHILLIES HOTEL AND FAMILY RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT OMALLOOR - (FAMOUS FOR CHILLY CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - ARYA BHAVAN, LOCATED IN PATHANAMTHITTA - (FAMOUS FOR SOUTH INDIAN FOOD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - A-ONE RESTAURANT, LOCATED IN PATHANAMTHITTA - (FAMOUS FOR BIRIYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - IMAANZ RESTAURANT, LOCATED IN PATHANAMTHITTA - (FAMOUS FOR SHAWARMA IS A TYPE OF SANDWICH MADE FROM MEATOF(LAMB, CHICKEN, BEEF),CHOPPED VEGETABLES AND WRAPED IN BREAD)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(381, 14, 31, 1661, 'Telangana', 'INDIA', 'RANGAREDDY', 'kans-grass-204147_640.jpg', 'kans-grass-204147_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Located in the Indian state of Telangana, Rangareddy is a district, which was formed on 15th August, 1978. The city of Hyderabad serves as the administrative centre of this destination. Situated in the central part of the Deccan Plateau, the destination, on the north is bounded by Medak district and on the south by Mahaboobnagar district. On the east, the destination is surrounded by Nalgonda district, while on the west lies Gulbarga district. According to the history, the destination until 1948 was under the rule of Nizams of Hyderabad. Formerly, the district was known as Hyderabad rural district, however later it was renamed as K.V. Ranga Reddy district. This new district was formed from the twin cities of Hyderabad and Secunderabad along with some urban areas of Hyderabad district. Owing to the strong influence of Hyderabad and Secunderabad, the destination has been a melting point of different cultures, languages, traditions, religions, civilisations and races. Mostly a cosmopolitan urban culture can be seen in this district due to the migration of people from different parts of India to this region for academic and educational purposes. Some of the most prominent attractions of the region include Shamirpet Lake, Maheshwaram, Anantagiri Hills and Chilkur. The best time to explore this destination is between October and February.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Rangareddy has something for every traveller, from luxury hotels to budget accommodations.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The Rajiv Gandhi International Airport is the nearest airbase to Rangareddy connecting it to various major cities of India and abroad</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - The Vikarabad Junction Railway Station serves as a major train link to other cities and states of India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Tourists can board buses, which operate from cities like Hyderabad and Secunderabad to reach this district.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', '');
