(382, 14, 31, 743, 'Kerala', 'INDIA', 'THRISSUR', 'elephants-743304_1280.jpg', 'elephants-743304_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Thrissur is one of the oldest cities in Kerala. The legend says, the city was the town created by Lord Parasurama the 6th incarnation of Lord Vishnu soon after formation of Kerala, by creating a large Shiva temple. The entire city is formed around the grand Shiva temple known as Vadakumnathan Temple. The city&#39;s original name was Thir-Shiva-Perur meaning the sacred city of Lord Shiva, which got later shortened as Thrissur. The temple is in the centre of a mega roundabout that is of 64 acres. This round is known as Swaraj Round and the giant square in front of the temple is known as Thekkinkad Maidan. All roads of Thrissur connect to this. Perhaps when Indians think of Thrissur, the first image would be the famous Thrissur Pooram festival, the most colourful and spectacular temple festival of Kerala. This is also known as largest temple festival in India. The festival is at the Vadakkumnathan temple grounds, in April or May. The city is equally famous for the final celebrations of the Onam festival, which is the national festival of Kerala. It hosts the famous Pulikali during Onam celebrations in August or September (depends on Malayalam calendar). Apart from festivals and culture, Thrissur is also well known as one of the best shopping centres in Kerala for silks and gold ornaments. The city is also known as Entrepreneurial City, due to presence of large number of entrepreneurs working in various trades.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Thrissur has a number of big and small hotels guest houses and luxury resorts that have good accommodation. Most of the renowned hotels are mainly located in the centre of the city. There are a few Dharamshalas that have economical accommodation. The Kerala Tourism Department has its hotel in Thrissur that offers good and economical accommodation. Prior booking needs to be done.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Cochin International Airport is the nearest airport to Thrissur, which is about 55 kms away. &nbsp;All international, domestic and chartered flights are available here.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail</strong> - Thrissur railway station is a huge broad gauge station that connects to all major cities in North and South India. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- National Highway 47 and State Highway 22 connect Thrissur to Palakkad, Kalady, Malappuram, Kochi, Calicut, Kunnamkulam etc. State Highway 49 connects Thrissur to its nearby temple town, Guruvayur.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Thrissur has a big bus stand that connects the city to nearby cities such as Palakkad, Ernakulum, Mysore, Calicut, Tiruvantapuram, Kochi etc. Plenty of private and KSRTC buses are available to and fro from the city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Buses, auto rickshaws, taxis and even bikes are available for internal commuting. A lot of sightseeing options are nearby city and can be accessed by walking as well.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - THRISSUR - {FAMOUS FOR IDIYAPPAM IS A BREAKFAST DISH MADE FROM RICE FLOUR ; ACHAPPAM IS A SNACK MADE FROM COCONUT MILK, EGGS, SESAME SEEDS, CUMIN SEEDS AND SUGAR ; KUZHALAPPAM IS A SNACK &nbsp;PREPARED BY DEEP FRYING ROASTED RICE FLOUR &nbsp;WITH ONION, GARLIC, SESAME SEEDS AND CUMIN SEEDS}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - HOTEL BHARATH, LOCATED AT CHEMBOTTIL LANE, NEAR ELITE HOTEL - (FAMOUS FOR PAYASAM IS A SWEET DISH MADE FROM RICE, MILK, SUGAR, CARDAMOM, SAFFRON, PISTACHIOS OR ALMONDS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - MADURAI VEGETARIAN, LOCATED AT THRISSUR - SHORNUR ROAD, PERINGAVU - (FAMOUS FOR MANGO AND APPLE SHAKE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - GOAL FACE, LOCATED AT TRICHUR-PALGHAT ROAD, PULIKKAN MARKET, PARAVATTANI - (FAMOUS FOR EGG POROTTA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - ALANKAR, LOCATED AT POST OFFICE ROAD, VELIYANNUR - (FAMOUS FOR PAROTTA &nbsp;AND BEEF FRY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - BBQ SQUARE, LOCATED AT PRESIDENCY SHOPPING COMPLEX, NEAR JAYALAKSHMI, POOTHOL ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR BEEF KEBAB)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - ARABIAN GRILL, LOCATED AT COLLEGE ROAD, EAST FORT - (FAMOUS FOR GRILLED CHICKEN)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n8 - FOOD VILLAGE RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT MURIAMTHOD,VALAPPAD - {FAMOUS FOR (PALAPPAM IS A TYPE PANCAKE MADE FROM RICE BATTER AND COCONUT MILK) AND MUTTON BIRYANI}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>9 - NANDINI VEGETARIAN RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT OPPOSITE POST OFFICE, EAST NADA, GURUVAYOOR - (&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;FAMOUS FOR PANEER BUTTER MASALA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>10 - HOTEL NEW GOPI, LOCATED AT AMBAKKADAN JUNCTION, ST THOMAS COLLEGE RD, EAST FORT - (FAMOUS FOR VADA &nbsp;AND IDLY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>11 - HONEY SWEETS, LOCATED AT NEAR MOTHER HOSPITAL, PULLAZHI, OLARIKKARA - (FAMOUS FOR FRUITJUICES)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(383, 14, 31, 1660, 'Arunachal Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'UPPER SUBANSIRI (DAPORIJO)', 'rainforest-49878_1280.jpg', 'rainforest-49878_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Paddy Fields, rainforests with bamboo trees along with beautiful Subansiri River flowing along the town, Daporijo is a small town on the way from Ziro to Along. Daporijo is a scenic town situated 600 meters above the sea level in the upper Subansiri district of the north eastern state of Arunachal Pradesh. Daporijo is typically a good town to stopover on the route of Along to Ziro for a break, otherwise, the town does not have much to offer to its tourists. The town is known for its varied ethnic cultures succinct at one place. River Subansiri a tributary of Brahmaputra gives a panoramic view flowing in the immediate vicinity of the town. This is a home of people of different tribes like Tagin, Galo, Hilmiri etc. one of the oldest being Mishmi, which are believed to have existed since the Mahabharata era. Varied tribes at one place enrich the town that also celebrates many local festivals. Bamboo handicrafts or colourful costumes are some special take away things from this place.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Daporijo does have good hotels and lodges which can best suit one&rsquo;s budget, but very few in numbers.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Flight</strong> - The nearest airport to Daporijo is Lilabari Airport which is 260 kms away from the town. Visitors can hire a cab or taxi to reach Daporijo. Lilabari also offers helicopter services up to Ziro which is 155 kms away from Daporijo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Road</strong> - Visitors choose to visit Daporijo on their way to major destinations. One can reach the town of Daporijo using buses from either Itanagar via Ziro or Lilabari via Bazzar. Govt. buses are generally overcrowded and breakdown often, so prefer private buses or a cab/taxi for the comfortable journey.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Train</strong> - The nearest railway station to Daporijo is Dibrugarh town railway station which is 87 kms away. Major station nearest railway station is Silapathar Station in Assam which is about 200 kms from the Daporijo town.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- There are bus services and taxis that are used to commute within the town. One can also walk to explore the local market.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(384, 14, 31, 1653, 'Uttarakhand', 'INDIA', 'UTTARKASHI', 'quinault-1376934_640.jpg', 'quinault-1376934_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Uttarkashi is a beautiful district perched at an altitude of 1158 mts above sea level. Himachal Pradesh and Tibet lie on its north, while the Chamoli District is located in the east. The place holds immense religious significance for the Hindus and is referred to as the &lsquo;Kashi of North&rsquo; as well as the &lsquo;Town of Temples&rsquo;. Two of the Four Holy Shrines of Hindu the &#39;Char Dham&#39;, are situated here, as is the chief source of the holiest river of Hinduism, the Ganges. There is a sense of purity in the air here, with all the spirituality and natural surroundings that are bestowed upon this land. Uttarkashi is one of the younger parts of Uttarakhand, formed in 1960. There is an uncanny purity about the place, making it one of the most visited cities of religious relevance in the area. While lakes and temples are in great numbers, the whole aura of religion is not over powering. Uttarkashi gives a sense of heightened divinity and an out of body experience, and it is one of the fewest places doing so, even on the trekking routes it has to offer.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Uttarkashi being a pilgrimage town is replete with hotels, luxury resorts, rented accommodations, inns and what not. From the cheapest possible rate, to the luxurious and all encompassing price of more than ten grand a night, Uttarkashi as a tourist destination leaves the tourists spoilt for choice. The only issue remains that one must book everything well in advance, at least a good 2 months in advance, as the summer and monsoon months are the heaviest in terms of tourist influx in the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest airport to Uttarkashi is the Jolly Grant Airport of Dehradun, which is located at a distance of 183 kms. The airport is well connected to the Indira Gandhi International Airport of New Delhi by regular flights.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail</strong> - Rishikesh and Haridwar railway stations are the closest to the destination. Both these railway stations are well connected to major Indian cities like Mumbai, Delhi, Howrah, and Lucknow by regular trains.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Uttarkashi is well connected to cities like Dehradun, Rishikesh, Haridwar, and Mussoorie by regular buses. State and private owned buses are available to Uttarkashi from these places.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - The travelling in the mountains is a bit of a stressful trip, with the steep terrain causing slow speeds and a bit of road sickness. If not acquainted with the hills, make sure to go for a more comfortable vehicle, to make the ride easier. Ample of travel agents in the city provide transportation. Bargain is must, but the deals in packages are usually good enough for trips.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - KIRAN SWEETS, LOCATED IN UTTARKASHI&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; - (FAMOUS FOR RASGOOLLAS AND MILKCAKE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - SADAH BAHAR RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT MUKHEM RENGE - (FAMOUS FOR ALOO PARATHA AND CHOLAE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - MANISH FAST FOOD CENTRE, LOCATED AT MAIN BUS STAND - (FAMOUS FOR NOODLES, PAKORAS)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(385, 14, 31, 738, 'gujarat', 'INDIA', 'VADODARA', 'cassia-pink-238643_640.jpg', 'cassia-pink-238643_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Vadodara or Baroda, situated on the banks of the river Vishwamitri was earlier the capital city of the Gaekwad state. Archaeological remains dating back to two thousand years around the river Vishwamitri clarify that there was a small settlement known as the Ankottaka, near a grove of Akola trees, which is now called Akota. Then a kilometre down east, a locality came up near a thick forest of vad or Banyan trees. This area was called Vadapadraka. In the place of Vadapadraka, today&#39;s Vadodora has come up. Vadodara is bestowed with some of the best tourist attractions of Gujarat. Known for its royal kingdoms, rich traditions and glorious past, the city is not just for the regular archaeology hunters but also for those who want a respite from the busy city life. Vadodara city has got some interesting places which are ideal getaways for a memorable weekend, a fun trip with friends or for a quick escapade. Vadodara is the third most populated city in the Indian state of Gujarat after Ahmedabad and Surat. Vadodara is famous for its palaces, parks, temples and museums. Vadodara is number one industrial city of Gujarat. Vadodara is also called as &#39;Sanskari Nagari&#39; for its rich culture traditions. Vadodara is one of India&rsquo;s most cosmopolitan cities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>A wide range of accommodation facilities are available in this city, given the fact that it is the 3rd largest city in the state of Gujarat. Budget hotels, mid range hotels and luxurious hotels are all available in this city. One would be able to find a shelter even without pre booking their rooms.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The Vadodara Airport or Civil Airport Harni is a domestic airport situated at the north east of the city in the suburb of Harni. There are regular flights to Mumbai, New Delhi, Bangalore, Kolkata, Hyderabad and other cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail</strong> - Vadodara Railway Station is the main station of the city. It is connected to New Delhi via Ratlam, Kota and Mathura and to Ahmedabad and Mumbai.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Vadodara is connected to Delhi, Gandhinagar and Mumbai through National Highway 8 and also to Ahmedabad and other cities in Gujarat through the Indian National Expressway, Vallabhipur Transportation Cooperative Society or VTCOS owned buses, operated by VTPL are the main road transport facility available in Vadodara.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Within the city public transport vehicles like buses, auto rickshaws and taxis are available for telecommuting buses has made public transportation quite easy. The popular vehicles amongst the public are cars, scooters, motorcycles and bicycles. The VITCOS City Buses take you to all parts of the city and the VITCOS Bus Stand is right opposite to the Railway Station, these buses are also cheap.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - Vishal Sandwich, near Baroda High School in Alkapuri - (famous for Samosa, &nbsp;Sandwich)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">2 - South Corner, Race Course Circle - (famous for masala dosa, onion rava masala dosa and idli bhaji)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">3 - Jay Mahakali Sev Usal, Nehru Bhavan, Kirti Stambh, Palace road - (famous for &nbsp;masala cold drink and fast food items)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">4 - Vanity Restaurant, Near Sardar Patel Statue, Sayajiganj - (famous for veg paneer roll, cheese sandwich, fruit jiuce, rice pulao)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">5 - Khan Baba, Ayesha Park, Near JP Police Station, Tandalja Road - (famous for varities of keeab)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">6 - Night Food Court, Mangal Pandey Rd, Fatehgunj - (famous for Dhokla, Dhosa, Kathiyawadi)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">7 - Ustad Miyaan, Shopping center, Vishwas Colony, Alkapuri - (famous for paneer kebab, cheese)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">8 - Jojo&#39;s Restaurant, Fatehgunj Main Rd, Jayesh Colony - (famous for chicken momos, hot and sour soup and thukpa)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">9 - Hariyali Restaurant, vrundavan heights, near parivar char rasta, waghodia - (famous for punjabi thali)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">10 - Rangoli Restaurant, Fatehganj Main Rd, Jayesh Colony - (famous for &nbsp;butter chicken)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">11 - Vishal Sandwich, Kashi Vishweshwar Town Ship, Nr Swagat Restaurant, Chikuwadi - (famous for samoosa and sandwiches)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">12 - Jashan, Race Course Rd, Abhishek Colony, Vadiwadi - (famous for chicken kadhai, chicken Tikka Masala, Kabab and Pathani Chicken)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">13 - Rasthal Gujarati Thali, Bhagwandas Chamber Opposite Ciuit House RC, RC Dutt Rd, Jetalpur - (famous for gujarati thali)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">14 - Sasumaa Gujarati Thali, RC Dutt Rd, Alkapuri - (famous for Gujarati dal kadhi)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">15 - Zaafaroon,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Shivalay Apartment, Haribakti Extension,, Old Padra road - (famous for &nbsp;south Indian food)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">16 - Santushti Shakes,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ashok Apartment, Opposite Sadar Bazar, Jayesh Colony - (famous for varities of shakes)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">17 - Gokul Thal Restaurant, Blanka Complex, Old Padra Rd,Opposite Raj Laxmi Society, Chikuwadi, Haripura - (famous for Gattae ki subji, Dam allo and makai paneer)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">18 - Cream Centre Veg Restaurant, &nbsp;Inorbit Mall Earth Complex, Old Padra Road, Near Malhar Point - (famous for Chole-Bhatura and chocalate icecream)</p>\