ous for punjabi thali)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">31 - Jay Hind Restaurant, Raopura road Opposite Kumar Shala, &nbsp;Jambubet - (famous for Sabudana Khichdi, Sabudana Vada and Sev Usal)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">32 - Regal The Family A C Restaurant, Bell-baug Shopping Centre, Near Railway Station - (famous for mutton masala chicken)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">33 - Rajasthan Ice cream Parlour, PRATHAMESH PLAZZA, NEHARU BHAVAN, KIRTI STAMBH - (famous for Mahakali Sevusal )</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">34 - Dawat Pure Veg Restaurant,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ivory Terrace, Opposite Circuit House, Alkapuri - (famous for punjabi food)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">35 - The Goodies Cafeteria, Gol Bungalow, Next To Post Office, Behind Kalyan Cafe, Sarod, Sayajigunj - (famous for malai kofta &amp; butter naan)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">36 - Rajasthan Ice cream Parlour, Aram Complex, Kirtistambh, Near Nehru Bhavan - (famous for Malai kulfi)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">37 - Saya Ji Garden, University Road Baroda, Gujarat State Highway 11, Fatehganj - (famous for paneer tikka and cheese naan)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">38 - Angeethi, Near Natubhai Circle, Hari Nagar - (famous for punjabi thali)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">39 - Gangaur Sweets, Jetalpur Rd, Gold Craft, Opposite Chiikoowadi, Vishwas Colony, Alkapuri - (famous for sweets, fresh farsans, dhokla, Methi peda and khandwa, jalebis, thepla)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">40 - Kachori Parlour, Dex Plaza, Waghodia Rd, Near Zaver Nagar Bus Stand, Prabhat Nagar - (famous for bhel kachori and mutter kachori)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">41 - Gandhi Khaman House, Lalbahdur Shopping Center, Harni Rd, Amit Nagar, Saikrupa society, Karelibagh&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;- (famous for KhamanDhokla, sev khamni, samosa Kajuwad)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">42 - Jay bhavani vadapav, opp shakti farsan, ellora park - (famous for gujarati snacks like khaman,dokla, fafda)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">43 - Madhav Kathiyawadi Restaurant, Rushab corners, opposite union bank, Nizampura - (famous for Bajri&#39;s Rotla, Sev Tamoto Sabji , Khachadi , Kadhi)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">44 - Sagar Restaurant&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Kothi Rd, Mandvi - (famous for undhiyu, poori-sabji and shrikhand)<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(386, 14, 31, 732, 'Andhra Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'VISAKHAPATNAM', 'ASA.jpg', 'ASA1.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Known for its pristine beaches, natural beauty and scenic landscapes along with a rich cultural and historical heritage, Visakhapatnam, better known as Vizag is a port city and a gem of South India. Visakhapatnam is a perfect tourist destination with a rich flora and fauna, sceneries around beaches made up of small hills, religious and cultural significance as well as a dynamic past. One can witness experiences of all types from bird watching, to enjoying a dynamic natural terrain, churches, and temples and so on. Visakhapatnam is the true spot where one can find the beauty of Andhra. Lapped by the Bay of Bengal on the eastern part of Andhra Pradesh, lies the beach city, Visakhapatnam. This city has beautiful hill ranges caves, valleys, temples, lakes and cool beaches. The district has many tourism spots that will definitely be exciting, enriching and refreshing experience. It is one of the fastest growing cities in Asia. It has many tourism spots that represent the Culture and Heritage of the true India. No one should miss to see the Cultural constructions built during the age of kings who ruled this region. Visakhapatnam is primarily an industrial city and also the largest city in Andhra Pradesh. It attracts large numbers of tourists because of its unspoiled beaches, the caves and scenic areas. It is also often considered as the Goa of the East Coast. The stunning landscape also contributes to the popularity of Visakhapatnam tourism.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There is a whole range of places to stay in Visakhapatnam for every kind of budget holder. Since Visakhapatnam is big on heavy industry it entertains a lot of business travel. Visitors can find variety of luxurious hotels, mid-range and budget hotels.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The Visakhapatnam Airport is located 7 kms from the city. It is a domestic airport and has daily flights from Hyderabad and Delhi and also flights from Calcutta and Chennai.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail</strong> - Visakhapatnam Junction is on the main broad gauge railway line from Calcutta to Chennai that runs along the coast. There are many connections available from other parts of the country including Delhi, Hyderabad, Bangalore, Chennai, Kolkata and Vijayawada.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Visakhapatnam is connected to Chennai and Kolkata by NH 5. Private buses and State Roadways buses service areas in and around Andhra Pradesh and connect Vizag to neighbouring places like Behrampore and Puri in Orissa. The state transport buses are really almost the very basic in four-wheel travel. More comfortable bus travel by way of Volvo buses that ply the route to Vizag are from Hyderabad, Chennai, Kolkata and Vijayawada.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Local transportation is available in the form of buses, cycle rickshaws, autos and taxis. The Andhra Pradesh State Road Transport Corporation operates buses in and around the city. It has express and deluxe buses along with luxury coaches which offer all kinds of amenities to their passengers. Apart from this, taxis and autos are easily available and cheap car rentals and chauffeur driven cars are also a good way to get around the city. For the more adventurous, bicycle rentals are also available.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - Visakhapatnam- [famous for Dosas, Idlis, Upmas Murri Mixture, Pickles and Chutneys, Booralu, Pulihara, Appadams, &nbsp;Laskora Undalu (coconut laddu) Sunnundallu, Pachadimade of vegetables, Pappu Koora(Lentil based dish), Vepudu(crispy fried vegetables) and Garelu (A type of Vada)]&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - Chyna Tang,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Chitralaya, Jagadamba Junction - (famous for schezwan sliced chicken, veg Manchuria, egg fried rice)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - Venkatadri Vantillu, Waltair Main Rd, Balaji Nagar, Asilmetta - (famous for south Indian food and sweet pongal and kesari puri)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(387, 14, 31, 1661, 'Telangana', 'INDIA', 'WARANGAL', 'temple-343934_640.jpg', 'temple-343934_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Warangal is a district located in the southern state of Telengana in India, and was the capital of the Kakatiya Kingdom that ruled from 12 to 14th century A.D. Warangal was also referred to as Orguguallu or Omtikonda in olden times, due to the presence of an enormous hillock that is evidently carved out of a single stone. Warangal City is located in Warangal District, which also comprises of Hanamakonda and Kazipet. Various architectural masterpieces such as the Warangal Fort prove to be popular attractions for tourists, and it is believed that Prola Raja of the Kakatiya dynasty was behind the construction of this picturesque city. Marco Polo, the famed Italian traveller, speaks of Warangal in his travel diaries and his writings regarding the place reflect the cultural and administrative excellence brought about during the reign of the Kakatiyas. Warangal has a primarily agrarian economy and crops such as red chillies, tobacco, cotton and rice are cultivated to a large extent here. The city boasts of a population of just under a million inhabitants. Warangal attracts a huge number of tourists throughout the year due to factors such as its historical significance, the variety of wonderful monuments found in the city, wildlife sanctuaries and impressive temples. The best season to visit would be between October and March.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Due to its immense popularity Warangal enjoys among tourists, accommodation in the city can be troublesome if not sorted out beforehand. Budget hotels that charge up to Rs. 750 per room are available throughout the year. Deluxe rooms with air conditioning cost around Rs. 1200 for a room, and many such dwellings can be found in the vicinity of the Warangal Fort. Luxury Resorts are an alternative for those willing to spend around Rs. 3000 to 4000 per day. Internet access in the rooms, a swimming pool and a multi cuisine restaurant are some of the features one can experience in these lavish resorts.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Warangal doesn&#39;t have any personal airport but the closest one is Rajiv Gandhi International Airport of Hyderabad.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Warangal has well established railway station and also connected to all India and lies on South Central Railway zone so, one can easily reach here via rail route.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Warangal is well connected to NH 202 so one can easily get in here via road by personal vehicle or hired taxi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Warangal is well connected to APSRTC so one can easily get bus from any major city of Telangana towards it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Hourly buses and taxis are available. Buses are the cheapest mode however.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - WARANGAL - [FAMOUS FOR HYDERABADI BIRYANI, GUDDU PULUSU MADE FROM EGGS, GOLICHINA MAMSAM (SPICY MUTTON FRY) and OORRU KODI PULUSU(CHICKEN CURRY), VEG DISHES ARE MIRCH KA SALAN, AND ULAVACHARU, GONGURA CHANA DAL (CHANA DAL COOKED IN &nbsp;SPICES AND TEMPERED WITH MUSTARD AND CURRY LEAVES, BACHALI KURA IS MADE FROM SPANICH AND TAMARIND PASTE, PACHI PULUSU IS A VARIETY OF &nbsp;RASAM OF SPICY- SOUR FLAVOR, COOKED WITH TAMARIND, ONIONS AND CHILIES, ARINTKAYA BANANA PULUSU OR VEPUDU AND ONKKAYA BRINJAL PULUSU, SNACKS LIKE SAKINALU, OR CHAKINALU MADE FROM RICE &nbsp;FLOUR AND SESAME SEEDDS, &nbsp;SWEETS LIKE JALEBIS, PHARDA PHENI IS SUGAR COATED WAFER SWEET ,KHEER AND SEVAYIN, MADUGULU MADE FROM MILK AND BUTTER, SUGAR&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(388, 14, 31, 743, 'Kerala', 'INDIA', 'WAYANAD', 'munnar-1639120_640.jpg', 'munnar-1639120_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Wayanad is one of the fourteen districts in Kerala and lies between the Kannur and Kozhikode districts. It is a very famous tourist destination primarily because of its location. Situated among the lush green mountains of the Western Ghats, the natural beauty of Wayanad is still in its pristine form. The place has a striking beauty that is a treat for sore eyes. It is little wonder then that tourists from far and wide travel each year to Wayanad. The place also sees plenty of corporate crowd coming for a weekend break to relax and rejuvenate themselves. In fact, Wayanad is the ideal place to search for peace and satisfaction that is otherwise missing from our day to day lives. Replete with enchanting waterfalls, historical caves and comfortable resorts and home stays, this popular town is famous for its spice plantations and wildlife. Among the prettiest areas of Kerala, Wayanad has a multitude of options for its visitors. Part of a forest reserve, Wayanad is located on the border of Tamil Nadu and Kerala. The entire region is completely green with hilly ranges and wildlife including Tholpetty in the North, Muthanga in the east bordering with Tamil Nadu, Kalpetta in the south and Mananthvadi in the northwest and Sultan Bathery in the east. Walking through the sprawling spice plantations, taking that trek into the pre historic caves and experiencing a resort holiday are one of the many things one can do to get a taste of Wayanad. A great place to spot wild elephants, cool breeze, beautiful scenery, Wayanad is guaranteed to please your travel senses. Overall it is a perfect weekend idea from cities of South India.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Pick home stays and resorts for a comfortable night cap, and a luxurious in house frolic. Although mid range hotels are hardly found in this district, tourists can also stay in cottages and 3 star hotels with ample facilities as well as deluxe.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The airport nearest to Wayanad is in Kozhikode. Kozhikode is about 75 kms from Kalpetta and 100 kms from Wayanad.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - The railway station nearest to Wayanad is in Kozhikode and there are many major towns and districts that the trains stop at before reaching Kozhikode. Kozhikode railway station is well connected to the rest of the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Wayanad is well connected with other cities via national highways. There are intersections from Kozhikode, Kannur, Ooty and Mysore leading to Wayanad. However, one has to be well stocked with foods and drinks as you may not find many restaurants about 100 kms from Wayanad.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Autos and taxis are the best way to travel. The hotels and resorts also arrange for car rentals complete with guide and maps.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1- WAYANAD - {FAMOUS FOR KILIKOODU IS A SNACK MADE WITH VERMICELLI, VEGETABLES, CHICKEN, MUTTON OR FISH ; MORU KOOTAN IS A DISH MADE WITH VEGETABLES LIKE ASH GOURD, PUMPKIN, RAW BANANAS, CARROTS, YAM, OR COLOCASSIA (CHEMBU)}<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - JUBILEE RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT MAIN ROAD, SULTAN BATHERY - (FAMOUS FOR BIRIYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - CLAYHUT A VILLAGE RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT OPPOSITE NEW BUSSTAND KALPETTA - (FAMOUS FOR PRAWNS CURRY WITH CHAPATHI OR RICE AND RASAM( IS A TYPE OF SOUP MADE FROM LENTILS, TOMATOES, TAMARIND PULP) AND BUTTERMILK}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - UDUPI VEGETARIAN RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT MALABAR HILL HIGHWAY - (FAMOUS FOR PAROTTA AND CHANNA BATURA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - KALPAKA VEGETARIAN RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT POLICE STATION RD, SATHRAMKUNNU, SULTAN BATHERY - (FAMOUS FOR MASALA DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - DENNYS COFFEE HOUSE, LOCATED AT OPPOSITE GOVT. LP SCHOOL LAKKIDI POST - (FAMOUS FOR JACK FRUIT CAKE)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(389, 14, 31, 1660, 'Arunachal Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'WEST KAMENG (BOMDILA)', 'trekking-1742821_640.jpg', 'trekking-1742821_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">West Kameng, located in the state of Arunachal Pradesh is a beautiful district and is one of the largest districts of the state. Bomdila is the district headquarters and major area of the region is covered with the Himalayas. The highest peak in the district is Kangte. West Kameng Travel guide is incomplete without a mention of its rich cultural and spiritual legacy. The region around the Kameng River is conventionally under the reign of the Mon kingdom, Bhutan, Tibet and the Ahom kingdom. The local tribes were strongly influenced by the Lamaism during the 7th century and this is when Lhagyala Gompa in Morshing was founded by the Kachen Lama. Bomdila is located in the West of Kameng district of Arunachal Pradesh. It is situated on the ranges of the eastern Himalayas. The scenic beauty of Bomdila attracts tourists to spend their holidays in the lap of nature. This town is also famous for its Buddhist monasteries and apple orchards. Nature and adventure lovers visit this place to explore the trekking trails. Bomdila offers its visitors the mesmerizing view of Kameng Valley and the Buddhist monasteries called as Gompas. Nechipu Pass, Kangto and Gorichan peaks are frequently visited by the tourists. The brief history of the city states that it was a part of the kingdom of Tibet. In 1873, the British officials brought this area under the state of Arunachal Pradesh. After independence, China invaded the area around Bomdila. The city reflects the heritage of Buddhist and Tibetan culture.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">There are some medium to budget accommodation options nearby West Kameng. The Bomdila Tourist Lodge is strategically located next to the DC Office and has the Upper and Lower monastery and the Handicraft Emporium close to it. The Govt. Circuit House is also a comfortable place to stay. Many mid range lodges can also be found which provide clean rooms and basic amenities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest International Airport from Bomdila is Lokpriya Gopinath Bordoloi International Airport, Guwahati, roughly 309 kms from the town. Bomdila city is closely linked to the airport which is located in Tezpur. It is about 160 kms away from Bomdila.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Rail</strong> - The nearest Railway Station is located at Tezpur named as Tezpur Railway Station, roughly 151 kms from Bomdila. Rangapara railway station is the nearest railway station from where one can get frequent trains to different locations.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Road</strong> - The road to Bomdila isn&#39;t very well kept and is extremely bad in a few patches. The ride takes nearly 6 hours unless there is a landslide, when it of course takes longer. Drive in for Tezpur or Rangpara by taxi or bus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Bomdila is a small town. Covering it on foot wouldn&#39;t be a problem. Tourists will have to hire a cab to reach the Upper Gompa.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(390, 14, 31, 1660, 'Arunachal Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'WEST SIANG (ALONG)', 'hohenschwangau-532864_640.jpg', 'hohenschwangau-532864_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">West Siang, located in the state of Arunachal Pradesh is an administrative district in the state. It is majorly populated by the Adi tribe which includes a large number of Aboriginal groups and subgroups such as the Shimongs, Milangs, Pasis, Karkos, Pangis, Minyongs, Padams, Ashings, Tangmas and Boris. The Adis are related to the Astro Mongoloid race, and are good looking, strong and dynamic. The territory was moved from West Siang district to East Siang district in 1989. After a decade, the district was partitioned to make Upper Siang district in 1999. The district got its name from the River Siang which originates from Tibet, where it is called Tsangpo. It passes through the entire area and descents down into the plains of Assam and becomes Brahmaputra. Nestled in the mountains of West Siang District in Arunachal Pradesh, Along is a beautiful town comprised of small villages. It is located near the borders of Assam and Arunachal Pradesh on the banks of two Rivers Yomgo and Sipu, tributaries of River Siang. It is situated at an altitude of 619 mts from the sea level. The scenic beauty of the town and the calm and tranquil valleys of the mountains take to a never ending journey of nature. It is also the headquarters of the West Siang District. Along is an ideal tourist destination for trekking, River Rafting and hiking.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">West Siang has some medium to budget accommodation options in the nearby areas. Along have many very reasonable accommodations. Nothing very fancy yet comfortable. The Circuit House is one of the best available accommodation facilities only if tourists are able to muster up a room.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest Domestic Airport is Chabua Airport, Dibrugarh; roughly five and half hour drive from the district headquarter Along.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail</strong> - The nearest Railway Station is Murkongselek Railway Station which is connected to all the major cities of Arunachal Pradesh and 131 kms from the city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - It is well connected with roadways, and National Highway 52 connects it to Pasighat. Buses and private transport are available to reach Along.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport </strong>- The local bus is an easy option. Covering the town by foot is also possible. Things will be easier if one has their own vehicle.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(391, 14, 31, 1658, 'Odisha', 'INDIA', 'BALASOREE (BALESHWAR) ', 'road-259815_1280.jpg', 'road-259815_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Balasore, a beach town, is located in the state of Orissa and is famous for Chandipur Beach and wonderful temples. Balasore is located near the coastal line and hence the beaches are connected with this town. The local people are basically dependent on farming, fishing and tourism for their livelihood. There are many temples located in this town, which are old and have beautiful architecture. The main attractions of this place include temples, historical places like tombs, palaces, nearby hills and beaches. All these things make this town worth exploring. Some of the old temples of this region are Gopinatha Temple, Lagula Narasimha Dev and Biranchinarayan Temple. These three temples make a trio and are located in 3 different directions in the city, hence protecting it from every side. Chandipur beach has many resorts and hotels, which provide the tourists with a place to stay during their visit and make their trip worthwhile by providing all the facilities. The tomb of a Sufi Saint located here is also famous and attracts many pilgrims from all over India. Balasore is a beach town and hence the weather of this place usually remains breezy and humid. Best months to visit this place are from September to March.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Balasore Town has some good hotels which provide decent accommodation with all luxurious amenities. There are so many resorts and beach-side hotels in Balasore, which provide world class facilities and sea side views to their customers. Ultra modern facilities, beach sports and delicious food are provided by many hotels and resorts of Balasore. One can avail the facility of economical to luxurious hotels as per their need. There are many hotels which provide guided tour of the place according to the package availed.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport to Balasore town is Bhubaneswar which is 199 kms. Bhubaneswar is connected to Kolkata, Mumbai, Delhi, Hyderabad, Raipur, and Nagpur by boarding flights.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Railway</strong> - Balasore has a rail head on the South Eastern Railway. Many major trains touch Balasore. There are also several local trains available between Balasore and its nearest towns and cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - There are many State transport buses (OSRTC) and private buses that connect the major towns of Orissa and neighbouring states to Balasore. Besides, National highways too pass through the district and run from Kolkata to Chennai.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Balasore is well connected by National Highway 5 while National Highway 60 connects Balasore to Jaleswar and West Bengal.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - BALESHWAR(BALASORE) - [FAMOUS FOR MACHA GHANTA( CHHINCHEDA AND CHHENCHEDA ARE( POPULAR FISH DISH MIXED WITH VEGETABLES) ; &nbsp;MACHA BESARA( IS ATTYPICAL ODIYAN FISH DISH THAT IS COOKED USING MUSTARD SAUCE) ; CHUNA MACHHA IS A SMALL FISH CURRY IT SERVE WITH ROTI AND RICE ; SWEETS ARE &nbsp;PANTUAS IS LIKE GULAB JAMUN, CHENNA PODA IS BASICALLY CHEESE THAT IS FRIED IN SUGAR]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - YUM CHINESE, AT MEGHADAMBRU - (FAMOUS FOR CHINESE FOOD AND VARITIES OF ICECREAM)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - BHOJAN, AT RAILWAY COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR VEG POKARA, PANEER TIKKA MASALA AND BUTTER NAAN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - THE RAINBOW, NEAR CHIDIAPOLO - (FAMOUS FOR UPMA, IDLI, DASA, DAHI BADE AND CHHOLE BHATURE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - JAGANATH PURI VEG STALL, AT MOTIGANG MARKET - (FAMOUS FOR PURI VAJI, AND VUGNIORIYA STYLE FOOD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - JAGADHATRI SWEETS, AT MOTIGANG MARKET - [FAMOUS FOR PATUAS (GULAB JAMUN)]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - HOTEL MARIDIAN, AT STATION SQUARE - (FAMOUS FOR HILSA PATHUDI(STEAM FISH PREPARED IN BANANA LEAF)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>8 - MEGABITES, NEAR CHANDIPUR SEA BEACH - (FAMOUS FOR BURGERS, FRENCH FRIES AND COFFEE)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(392, 14, 31, 1656, 'Nagaland', 'INDIA', 'WOKHA', 'mountains-1643627_6402.jpg', 'mountains-1643627_6403.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Wokha is a town that is situated in the state of Nagaland in the district of Wokha. The town of Wokha is well renowned for its cottage industries and one can see different industries indulging in wood works, pottery and weaving. One can purchase some of these traditional products as souvenirs. The entire region is hilly in nature and there are many fruit farms that are located along the slopes. The main inhabitants of the town are the Lothas and these people are known for their colourful dances and culture. One can also witness singing and other activities. Shanta is one of the main acts of the Lotha people. Many festivals are celebrated in the place and the most important ones are Pikhuchak and Tokhu Emong. There are numerous villages that are located nearby and they still have the remnants of traditional Lotha culture. The main villages are Yanthamo, Longidang, Longsachung, Longsa and Nrung Longidang. One can also purchase the traditional shawls that can be seen here and they are known as Opvuram for men and Longpensu for women. The mysterious Mount Tiyi is also present nearby and many legends and myths surround this place. One can get an excellent view of the villages from here.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>There isn&#39;t a whole variety of hotels. The few lodges are quite decent and very reasonable.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air</strong> - The town of Wokha has no airport of its own, and the Dimapur Airport serves as the gateway to this place. The airport is located at a distance of 162 kms and easily connected by taxis and shuttles.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Rail</strong> - Wokha has no rail head, and if planning to reach there by train Dimapur Railway Station would be the ideal place to disembark.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Road</strong> - The town mainly relies on road communication with NH 39 connecting it to Dimapur which is a major gateway to this place. Another way to reach this place is from the state capital Kohima which is 75 kms from this place. Nagaland State Transport buses and shuttle services are easily available from both these places.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(393, 14, 31, 739, 'Haryana', 'INDIA', 'YAMUNANAGAR', 'road-220058_12801.jpg', 'road-220058_12802.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Located in the state of Haryana, Yamuna Nagar is the headquarters of the district. The city is dotted with impeccable cleanliness and serene ambience and is growing at a fast pace. It is bounded by the 4 beautiful places, Ambala, Karnal, Himachal Pradesh and Kurukshetra. Yamuna Nagar travel guide is full of references to the places of immense historical significance. The city has emerged as a significant industrial place in the state. Sugarcane, rice, wheat and garlic are the major cash crops of the city which offers a source of livelihood to the local people. One of the renowned attractions of the place is Adi Badri which captivates large number of tourists round the year. Yamuna Nagar is a clean and prosperous industrial city mainly known for its plywood units. One of the cities of Haryana it is blessed to be located by the River Yamuna. Recently due to rapid urbanization, Yamuna Nagar is facing pollution crisis. It is bounded by Saharanpur in Uttar Pradesh in the east. Yamuna Nagar etched its importance in history. It had remained the residence of refugees who migrated to India after partition in I947. It was earlier known as &#39;Abdullahpur&#39; and was inhabited by 6000 people. Through archaeological survey Harappan stones and bricks were found from this region of Haryana.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Yamuna Nagar has some deluxe and medium to budget accommodation options which provide with all high class facilities which make tourists stay a reliable and memorable one.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Yamunanagar is well connected to all neighbouring cities and states by road network.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest Airport from Yamunanagar is Shaheed Bhagat Singh International Airport, Chandigarh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Bus</strong> - Haryana State Road Transport Corporation and private travel services connects all neighbouring states and cities with Yamunanagar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - Yamunanagar has its own railway station which connects to all major cities and neighbouring states.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', '');
