(394, 14, 31, 1656, 'Nagaland', 'INDIA', 'ZUNHEBOTO', 'nandi-hills-371597_640.jpg', 'nandi-hills-371597_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Zunheboto, located in central Nagaland is situated at a height of about 1800 mts above sea level. Its neighbouring districts are Mokokchung, lying in the east and Wokha lying in the west. Zunheboto is also the name of the district. While Zunhebo is the name of a flowering shrub having white leaves and sponge like ears containing sweet juice and &#39;To&#39; to mean &#39;On top of the hills&#39;. Zunheboto is a Sumi word. It is the sole urban locality in the district measuring around 1255 sq kms. The hills in Zunheboto vary in height from 1000 to 2500 mts. The name Zunheboto is derived from &lsquo;zunhebo&rsquo;, a white-leaved flowering shrub growing in the region which yields a sweet juice and &lsquo;to&rsquo; meaning hill top. Since the zunhebo plant is found in abundance in the region and the town is situated on the hills, it is named Zunheboto. Zunheboto is visited mostly for the bird sanctuary in the region and the forest range. Most of the people live in rural areas and subsist on agriculture. The three rivers flowing through the town are Tizu, Doyang and the Tsutha. The main festivals celebrated in Zunheboto are Tuluni and Ahuna. Since Zunheboto is located at a high altitude the region has a monsoon climate for the most part of the year. December and January are the coldest months of the year. Summers are generally warm.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Really affordable hotels and guest houses are available.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air</strong> - Like all the towns and villages of Nagaland, Zunheboto too does not have its own airport and the nearest one is located in Dimapur, about 80 kilometres away.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Rail</strong> - Dimapur is the railhead of Nagaland. To reach Zunheboto in train, one will have to reach the Dimapur railway station and take the road forward.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Road </strong>- Zunheboto lies along the National Highway 61 and thus is well connected to the rest of the state. Zunheboto is 152 kms from Kohima and 70 kms from Mokokchung. The Nagaland state transport buses are easily available from all these places to reach Zunheboto.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Private taxis can be booked. Nagaland State Transport buses and shuttle services are easily available from both these places.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(395, 14, 31, 1658, 'Odisha', 'INDIA', 'ANGUL', 'trees-1210028_6401.jpg', 'trees-1210028_6402.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">The city of Angul located at the heart of Odisha state is one of the most important commercial and industrial centres. Besides, it is also developing into a major tourist centre, owing to its lush green forests and pleasant ambiance, abundant wildlife, and beautiful tourist attractions and scenic locations. Availability of utility services, well developed transport system, strategic location, pleasant climatic conditions and industrial development have contributed majorly to the progress and increasing popularity of this city. The city of Angul has witnessed the rise and fall of several great and reputed dynasties. This city came under the rule of Bhaumakaras, Somavamsis of South Kosala, Gangas, Suryavamsis, Bhoi dynasty, Afghans of Bengal, and other rulers belonging to varied dynasties. Somanath Singh is believed to be the last ruler of Angul and he ruled from 1814 to 1847, for a period of about 33 years, until he was removed by the government. Due to its head strong and outspoken nature, he incurred the wrath of the British officials. Therefore, Angul came under the rule of the British government in the year 1848. The district of Angul, which was formerly a part of Dhenkanal district, came into separate existence on April 1, 1993. Though majority of the people living in Angul are Hindus, people belonging to other castes and communities also live together here in peace and harmony.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">There is no dearth of quality hotels and lodges for those looking for accommodation options in Angul city. With the latest technology and a wide variety of services, these hotels offer homely ambience and a memorable stay for the visitors. In addition, there are lodges that provide cost effective services to the residents as well as the tourists here. These hotels and lodges are located at prominent locations throughout the city, thus proving quite beneficial in terms of communication.</p>\r\n', '<p><br />\r\n<strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport for approaching the places of interest in the district of Angul is at Bhubaneswar, which is connected with major cities by Boeing flights.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail</strong> - Angul is a railhead on South Eastern Railways.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Situated on NH 42 at a distance of 160 kms from Bhubaneswar, the place is an important road junction of the State connected by regular bus services from Bhubaneswar, Cuttack, Dhenkanal, Sambalpur, etc.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport -</strong> The major modes of communication within the city include auto rickshaws and taxis.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(396, 14, 31, 1658, 'Odisha', 'INDIA', 'BALANGIR', 'leaf-warbler-300529_640.jpg', 'leaf-warbler-300529_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Balangir is an important commercial city with a rich cultural heritage. The place is famous for its beautiful setting with many old temples and shrines and the indigenous tribes that dwell here since time immemorial. This place still holds the past glory and charm of being the capital of Patnagarh, a princely state at one point of time. The name of the place comes from the words Balaram Garh, which is a fort constructed by the 19th king of Balangir, Balaram Deo. Tourism in Balangir is mainly due to the panoramic places that encompass the city. Jalia is a beautiful village surrounded by dense forests. This place is a popular spot for trekking. The river that passes through this scenic village makes this village a favourite spot for picnics. Balangir tourism presents diverse places of tourist attractions. Tourists will find ashrams, lakes, palaces, parks, temples and shrines belonging to various religions all in this city. The Sailashree Palace where once the royal family of Balangir resided is considered to be one of the best palaces in Odisha. One of the oldest lakes in Odisha Karanga Kata is a beautiful picnic spot too. The Municipality Board of Balangir has upgraded the place and introduced boating facilities here to boost tourism. The place also has beautiful gardens all around. Apart from sightseeing there are many more things you can do in Balangir. This city is popular for its Sambalpuri saris, dress materials and bed sheets. Balangir can be visited during the winter months which are from October to February.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Balangir, being a place for most of tourist visits, the stay for the guests of the city is accommodated with the best serviced hotels. There are a range of hotels that suits everyone&rsquo;s pocket. Catering of not only the local delicacies, the hotels also have varied varieties of food the rooms are spacious with the clean environment and keeping hygiene on the priority list.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Raipur in Chhattisgarh is the nearest airport. The nearest airport in the state is situated at Bhubaneswar. Bhubaneswar is around 321 kms away from Balangir.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The Balangir Railway Station is an important junction of South Eastern Railway that falls on the Jharsuguda Sambalpur Titlagarh line. The city is well connected to other parts of Odisha via a good network of trains.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Balangir is well connected by road. The state government owned buses are available from other cities and towns to reach Balangir. Air conditioned buses and taxi services are also available for transportation.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - PIZZAHOUSE, LOCATED AT NH201, INDRA NAGAR, PALACE LINE - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA AND BIRIYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - BALANGIR - {FAMOUS FOR PANTUA IS A DESERT MADE FROM KHOA &nbsp;AND SAFFRON ; CHAUL BARA IS A SNACK MADE FROM URAD DAL OR BLACK GRAM}</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(397, 14, 31, 1658, 'Odisha', 'INDIA', 'BARGARH', 'india-1453721_6401.jpg', 'india-1453721_6402.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Bargarh is a small but important city in Bargarh district of Odisha state. It is a municipality, famous for industries, business and tourism. Various ancient temples, natural sceneries and different cultural festivals in Bargarh attract lots of tourists every year. Being the business hub of Western Orissa, Bargarh is situated towards the western border of the state towards Chhattisgarh. The place was initially a fort and was initially called as the Baghar Kota, as derived from the inscriptions from 11th century AD. Bargarh has also witnessed early Buddhist settlement and have influenced the lifestyle of the people for a short span of time. Bargarh though has few tourist attractions but it is rich in its cultural heritage. Bargarh is famous for the Dhanuyatra that is said to the biggest open theatrical stage and depicts the Krishna Leela. The place is dotted with temples and also has Buddhist monasteries and caves that showcase the settlement of different cultures at different points in time at Bargarh.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">As Bargarh is an important business hub and tourist spot in Odisha, there is no scarcity for good hotels and restaurants in the city. There are several famous hotels and restaurants in Bargarh city that provide tourists delicious and quality food as well as standard accommodation facilities with warm services.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - Bargarh does not have an airport. Nearest airport is Raipur Airport at a distance of 206 kms from Bargarh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - Bargarh Road Railway Station connects Bargarh to major cities of the country. Tourists can easily get regular trains to Bargarh from other cities of the country. Bargarh Railway station is situated in the city and it belongs to East Coast Railway Zone, Sambalpur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Bus</strong> - Bargarh is also connected to other cities of the state through bus services. Nearest bus stand is Burla 32 kms away from Bargarh.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - GO-COOL, LOCATED AT CANAL AVE - (FAMOUS FOR CAKES, ICECREAM, PIZZA, BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - HAPPY HOURS, LOCATED AT SHREE GOPAL GOSHALA, BARGARH ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR CHEESE DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - MEHER SNACKS, LOCATED AT BHATLI ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(398, 14, 31, 1658, 'Odisha', 'INDIA', 'BARIPADA', 'railway-1677216_640.jpg', 'railway-1677216_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">At a distance of 248 kms from Kolkata and 256 kms from Bhubaneshwar, Baripada is a city, recognised by its beautiful culture and an essence of purity in nature. Baripada is also known as Dwitiya Srikhetra the Second Puri. Located in the state of Orissa in Mayurbhanj district, Baripada is a very beautiful city. In addition to being the commercial centre of the entire district, it is also very famous as a tourist spot and is located in close proximity to Simlipal, which is one of the most famous wildlife parks in India. Baripada is a heavenly place full of many breath taking scenic locations. Baripada has always been high up on the tourist&rsquo;s itineraries especially the foreign tourists due to its rich culture and heritage. Baripada city guide is full of references of the architectural marvels in and around the area. Baripada is also very popular for its ancient temples. One of the most prominent temples is the &ldquo;Lord Jagannath Temple&rdquo;, also known as &ldquo;Haribaldev Temple&rdquo; built by Baidyanath Bhanj in 15th century. Chariot Festival or Rath Yatra is the major attraction of Baripada. The city also organizes the second most popular Rath Yatra of Orissa, thus it is also known as &lsquo;Ditiya Srikhetra&rsquo;. Baripada is widely admired for its amazingly beautiful Art and Culture. It is famous for the Chhau dance form which is famous worldwide. Baripada is also known for its Bangripori &quot;tusser&quot; fabric, that can be found anywhere in its local markets.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Being an important tourist and commercial centre in Odisha, Baripada city attracts huge number of nature lovers and tourists from different parts of the country. There are plenty of accommodation options for the visitors in Baripada that they can choose as per their comfort, convenience and choice. Equipped with basic amenities and stylish interiors, these hotels and lodges offer the customers a memorable and pleasant stay. There are posh hotels with spacious rooms, as well as modest ones, to cater to the needs of the people belonging to all sections of the society. A stay in these hotels and lodges can help to relax, refresh as well as recharge.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- There are two airports which, almost at the same distance from Baripada. One is Biju Patnaik International airport in Bhubaneshwar at a distance of 256 kms and another is Netaji Subhash Chandra Bose International airport in Kolkata at a distance of 248 kms.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Baripada is well connected to close by cities like Balasore, Kharagpur, Jamshedpur, Cuttack, Bhubaneshwar and many others through frequent bus services, taxis, chartered buses and trains.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The city has its own railway station, but it is not a major one. Trains for Cuttack, Bhubaneshwar and other closer cities are available here. Tourists can simply get off to any major railway station near the city and choose to interchange for Baripada station afterwards.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Commuting within or outside Baripada is convenient and there are different modes of transportation available.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - BARIPADA - [FAMOUS FOR MUDHI MANSA( PUFFED RICE MIXED WITH MUTTON GRAVY)]</p>\r\n', ''),
(399, 14, 31, 1658, 'Odisha', 'INDIA', 'BERHAMPUR', 'ocean-931776_6401.jpg', 'ocean-931776_6402.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Berhampur is the name that the British colonialists gave the city. The city has recently been renamed as Brahmapur reflecting the Sanskrit influences in the original name of the city. While the efforts to Indian-ize the name are apparent, like all old habits, the name Berhampur remains for some unfathomable reason. The name literally translates into Lord Brahma&rsquo;s abode. The number of temples and the religious inclination of the locals justify the nomenclature of the city in the current day. Religious tourism in Berhampur contributes to the economy of the state. Berhampur located in the Ganjam district of Orissa, has been nicknamed as the city of silk. Berhampur is one of the largest and also oldest cities of Orissa. The cultural backdrop that creates the unique experience today is attributed to its past. The intricate silk saris called the Berhampur patta is a souvenir that is unique and reminiscent of the many influences that make the city what it is today. Handloom and jewellery showrooms dot the landscape of the city. Berhampur offers a beach lover&rsquo;s retreat like never before. The sights and sounds include much more than just the same old sun, sand and surf. Temples, culture, cuisine and theatre all unique to Berhampur make for a vacation that is beyond the bounds of a few days on the beach. Tourism in Berhampur is a versatile entity that offers a little getaway for every individuals dream. The best time to visit Berhampur would be between October and June when the weather is pleasant.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">a). Ganjam<br />\r\nGanjam is one of the prominent districts of Odisha. The name of the place is the name derived from &lsquo;Gan-i-aam&rsquo; which means the store house of food grains. Ganjam is situated on the bank of Bay of Bengal and hence is characterised by numerous exotic beaches which boost its tourism all round the year. Embellished with green vegetation punctuated with mighty mountains and mystic rivers, this beautiful place is rich in ancient remnants as well. Dotted with holy and ancient temples, Ganjam is a place where thousands of devotees throng to seek miracles from the supreme power. Tourism in Ganjam gains its momentum during several festivals like Dolo Yatra, Taratarini Mela, Danda Yatra and Thakurani Yatra which are held with huge congregation of devotees pouring in from different parts of the country. The exquisite handicrafts like stone carvings, bamboo crafts, wood carvings, appliques and brass designs add to the medals of glory of the district.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">There basically are budget hotels available in Berhampur with tariffs starting from approximately Rs 300 to Rs 1200. These provide basic amenities and value for every rupee that tourists will pay. Principal towns of Brahmapur and Ganjam have no dearth of hotels, lodges and guest houses.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Flight </strong>- Closest airport is Biju patnaik airport in Bhubaneshwar at a distance of 171 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Road </strong>- If on Gopalpur Ahemdabad road then NH 59 will take to Berhampur, NH 217 for Gopalpur Raipur route and NH 5 for Chennai Kolkata route. There is bus services which have been started to connect to urban locations to their outskirts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Train </strong>- Behrampur has its own railway station which also connects to the major cities of the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Water</strong> - Closest port is in Gopalpur. There is also an upcoming satellite at Bahunda mouth in Muhan further information about the commencement of the same is not available as yet.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Berhampur is well developed in transportation. Tourists can opt to take auto rickshaws, cycle rickshaws, buses or taxis as per the convenience and budget.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(400, 14, 31, 1658, 'Odisha', 'INDIA', 'BHADRAK', 'gleise-1066111_640.jpg', 'gleise-1066111_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Bhadrak is the only Municipality town of Bhadrak District. It serves as district headquarters and is most important town from administrative and economical point of view. The town is very well connected to rest of Odisha and India via train service. Its strategic location and good connectivity are certainly advantageous factors, which can propel it to greater prosperity in coming decades. Bhadrak is an ancient land located at a distance of 159 kms from the main city of Bhubaneshwar. Bhadrak is bounded by Baleshwar district in the north, Jajapur and Kendrapara in the west and Kendujhar district, in the south and Bay of Bengal in the east. The place has been separated from Balasore in the year of 1993 and formed another new district. River Salandi surpasses by this district and has added equally like the other older districts in all sphere of the place like cultural, economical, social and political field. The historical and religious consequences of the place are also well developed at the place. Tourists here explore the rich heritage of the region. Apart from the rich heritage the place is also known for the famous temple of goddess Maa Bhadrakali. In addition the place is also well known for the popular river Baitarani which is an adobe of lord Shiva. Orissa&#39;s marine &amp; agrarian affluence can be seen easily.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Visit the famous luxury hotels in Bhadrak that are known for serving the customers for decades. These hotels know how to provide luxurious experience to its customers at very affordable cost. This is why they are considered amongst most desirable hotels of Bhadrak city.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport around Bhadrak is Bhubaneswar Airport which is about 127 kms from Bhadrak.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The place is well connected through the rail connection. Bhadrak railways station is directly linked to Bhubaneswar, Kolkata, Delhi, Chennai, etc. One can get the train from major cities and towns of the place to reach the district easily.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Instead of Bhadrak tourists can a get a bus to Chandbali on regular basis which is about 42 kms away from Bhadrak.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - For travelling locally, tourists can anytime depend on auto rickshaws, which are available here in more than sufficient numbers.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - BHADRAK - [FAMOUS FOR MACHHER JHOL( IS AFISH STEW MADE FROM FISH POTATOAND TOMATOES), MANDA PITA( &nbsp;IS ASTEAMED PITHA PREPARED DURIND DURGA PUJA, &nbsp;PURNIMA), MATHAPULI IS A DESERT MADE FROM URAD DAL AND SUGAR SYRUP, OUU KHATTA IS A SOUR AND SWEET CHUTNEY, &nbsp;RASABALI( IS ASWEET DISH MADE FROM COTTAGE CHEESE AND MILK) ; HANDIA IS A RICED BASE BEER, KAKARA PITHA IS A SWEET CAKE MADE FROM WHEAT FLOUR, SUGAR, COCONUT), KHIRA SAGARA IS ASWEET DISH MADE FROM MILK, SUGAR, SAFFRON, CARDAMOM), KHIRAMOHANA IS A DESERT MADE FROM CHHENA AND SUGAR) ; ALU POTALA RASA IS A SPICY BASED CURRY MADE WITH POTALA AND ALU), CHAKULI PITHA IS A FLAT RICE BASED CAKE, CHANDARAKANTI IS A DESERT MADE FROM RICE FLOUR, SUGAR AND BUTTER]</p>\r\n', ''),
(401, 14, 31, 1658, 'Odisha', 'INDIA', 'BOUDH', 'buddha-1550589_640.jpg', 'buddha-1550589_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">The district of Boudh is situated in central part of the State. Earlier it was an integral part of Phulbani district, which was known as Boudh Kandhamal. It was raised to the status of a district headquarters of Odisha on January 02, 1994. Boudh is traversed by river Mahanadi and its tributaries, along which lie the extensive reverie fertile plains. The socio economic genesis of the people of Boudh lies in the agrarian economy which is due to large and extensive fertile plains suitable for cultivation. This district is famous for a large number of festivals, celebrated all round the year by the Hindus. They are either domestic festivals or public festivals. The domestic festivals generally cater to worshiping of family deities and observance of Ekadashis and Vrats. Public festivals on the other hand are a reason for merrymaking, melas and fun. They are religious ceremonies attended by a large number of men, women and children who come for worship as well as entertainment. Boudh is famous for its century old aesthetically built temples, ancient Buddha statues and caves. The mystic beauty of this place engulfs the visitors in its magical charm. Devotees and nature lovers will find this place exhilarating. The serenity of the place makes the people visit this place again and again.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">It can be stated that visiting Odisha is generally affordable for visitors. One of the important reasons behind this is the availability of cheap accommodation facilities. A good number of cheap hotels are available for visitors.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest Airport is at Bhubaneswar at a distance of 240 kms from Boudh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Road</strong> - Boudh is well connected with road and rail with other district headquarter and the state capital Bhubaneswar. One can come to Boudh via State Highway 1 &amp; 14 or by NH 42, via Angul and can travel a distance of 27 kms to reach Boudh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Train</strong> - Regular train services are available from Bhubaneswar to Boudh. To reach Boudh one has to get down at Rairakhole station.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(402, 14, 31, 1658, 'Odisha', 'INDIA', 'DEBAGARH  (DEOGARH)', 'falls-1572839_640.jpg', 'falls-1572839_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Deogarh or the abode of the Gods, is the headquarters of the sub division of the same name in the district of Santhal Parganas, and is located four miles to the South-east of Jasidih Junction on the main line of the Eastern Railway from Howrah to Delhi. There is a small branch line of the same railway from Jasidih to Deogarh. As a matter of fact, Deogarh is a far bigger and more important town than Dumka, the district headquarters. Deogarh or Devagriha has a large number of temples within the circumference of a few miles. The temple of Baidyanath or Shiva is the most important of all the temples and attracts a large number of pilgrims all the year round. District of Deogarh is situated in the Western region of the state having its Head Quarter at Deogarh. Deogarh town is located 90 kms to the East of Sambalpur town on NH 6. There are three important fairs, namely, Shri Panchmi mela held in January, Shivaratri mela held in March and the Bhadra Purnima mela held in September. Shivaratri mela is attended by many visitors in the course of a fortnight. A number of lodging houses is available for pilgrims.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Though Deogarh is a small district in comparison with other districts, but the status of the district basically belongs to the families of the Rajas &amp; Maharajas. So, the accommodations available here are also of royal quality. Though the number of star hotels can&rsquo;t be found, but numbers of good hotels are available in the district.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest airports for visiting places of interest in Deogarh district are at Bhubaneswar at a distance of 280 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- The nearest rail heads for Deogarh are at Sambalpur which is about 90 kms from Deogarh. The railway station at Deogarh is called Baidyanath Dham.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Deogarh town is 90 kms to the east of Sambalpur Town on NH 6. It is 115 kms from Rourkela &amp; 280 kms from Bhubaneswar.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- Passenger buses run regularly from Bhagalpur, Dumka, Patna, Gaya, Monghyr, and other places in Bihar to Deogarh.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Taxis and Tangas are available at Deogarh. Tangas are available at Jaisidih railway station but not taxis.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(403, 14, 31, 1658, 'Odisha', 'INDIA', 'DHENKANAL', 'pond-heron-1239856_1280.jpg', 'pond-heron-1239856_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Dhenkanal, situated at a distance of 99 kms from the capital city of Bhubaneswar, is a lovely place. Nature has played a great role in bestowing Dhenkanal with abundant natural beauty. The hamlet of Dhenkanal is a sun kissed land that is rich in the natural treasures of flora and fauna. The beauty of the place is due to the fact that it is endowed with hills, valleys and rivers. Dhenkanal is mainly known for its deep green forests and large wild animals like tigers and elephants. The place is a standing example of the fact that there is no better architect than nature itself. The landscape of Dhenkanal has a lot of manmade architectural splendours that accent its natural beauty. Dhenkanal tourism has several treasures in its kitty to offer the visitors. Dhenkanal is a place that carries great respect for its culture and religion. That is why there are several religious places in and around the district of Dhenkanal. The place has a lot of beautiful temples dedicated to various Hindu Gods. The best season to visit Dhenkanal is during the winter months of October to December, February and March.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Dhenkanal has some medium to budget accommodation options. The hotels are homely and laced with the modern amenities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\n<strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest airport to Dhenkanal is the Biju Patnaik Airport at Bhubaneswar. This prominent airport is connected by several flights to all major parts of the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The closest railway station to Dhenkanal is the bustling railway station situated at Cuttack. There are several trains that connect the Cuttack Railway Station to different parts of the state as well as country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Dhenkanal is connected through a network of National Highways and highways with the rest of the state.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - There are air conditioned taxis and regular taxis that can be hired for travelling in and around the township as well as go to nearby towns or cities. Dhenkanal is a place that has taxis for travelling short and long distances. Hence travelling in Dhenkanal by road is not a problem.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>1 - HENKANAL - [FAMOUS FOR BARA( IS PREPARED FROM BLACK GRAM DAL OR URAD DAL ALONG WITH RICE)]<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(404, 14, 31, 1658, 'Odisha', 'INDIA', 'GAJAPATI', 'peltophorum-pterocarpum-320142_640.jpg', 'peltophorum-pterocarpum-320142_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Gajapati district has been named after Maharaja Sri Krushna Chandra Gajapati Narayan Deb, the Ex-Raja Sahib of Paralakhemundi estate and the first Prime Minister of Odisha State who is remembered for his contribution in formation of a separate Odisha province and inclusion of Paralakhemundi estate in Odisha. Gajapati district came into being with effect from 2nd October 1992. Prior to this it was a part of Ganjam district. Ganjam district binds this district on the East, Rayagada district on the West, Phulbani districts on the North and Andhra Pradesh on the South. The mountains contain no exploitable mineral of economic value. However, the major economic minerals in the district are granite decorative stones found in some part of the Paralakhemundi Tahasil. The river Vansadhara and Mahendratanaya are two important rivers of Gajapati district. The river Vansadhara originated from Lanjigarh area of Kalahandi district and passes through Kashinagar block and flows southwards along the border of line of Gajapati district. The river Mahendratanaya has originated from the Mahendragiri range and flows in the westward direction through Rayagada block and then to southward direction through Gosani block. The major forest products are Timber, Bamboo, Hill Broom, Patala Garuda, Soap nut, Marsinga leaf, Dhatuki flowers, Kochila seeds, Genduli gum, Siali leaves and Kathalai etc.</p>\r\n', '<p>A large number of good and reasonable hotels are available in the district.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Train</strong> - There is no major rail communication to this district. One narrow gauge railway route from Naupada to Gunupur constructed in the year 1889 by the Maharaja of Paralakhemundi. It covers 93 kms of the district.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Gajapati is 30 kms far from Paralakhemundi and 153 kms far from Berhampur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air </strong>- Nearest Airport is in Bhubaneswar.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(405, 14, 31, 1658, 'Odisha', 'INDIA', 'JAGATSINGHPUR', 'india-995576_6404.jpg', 'india-995576_6405.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Jagatsingpur got the recognition of a district on 1st April 1994, which is situated at a distance of 60 kms from Cuttack. Jagtsingpur district has made Orissa&#39;s literature and culture brigh. There exists Paradeep Port and fertilizer factory in this district. Alika, Biluakhai, Kusumi, Kuanria and Lunijhara rivers belong to this district. Having a geographical area of 1759 sq kms, the Jagatsinghpur district is the smallest district in Odisha in terms of territorial location. Jagatsinghpur district has only one subdivision namely Jagatsinghpur. Jagatsinghpur district enjoys a temperate climate. Winters are cold, while summers are hot and humid. The District is prone to cyclonic rainfalls during the monsoons. The District is packed with many attractive places such as Paradeep Port, Paradeep, Paradeep Garh, Sarala Temple Jhankad and Garh Kujanga is some of the visiting places of the District. Gorakhanath Temple is one of the most attractive temples of the District. Jagannath Temple of Garoi is also a famous tourist spot visited by a large number of people from the world. The Major food crop grown in Jagatsinghpur district is paddy. Sugarcane, turmeric and cotton are the major commercial crops. The district enjoys rich fertile soil of the Mahanadi. &nbsp;A section of people is engaged in fishing as allied activity.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Jagatsinghpur offers the best and the most luxurious hotels in Paradeep. The area is well connected to the entire city of Paradeep and is for those who want to have the best of accommodation. With a lot of 4 and 5 star hotels, Jagatsinghpur is a hub of activity in Paradeep. Most travellers looking to see the best side of the city prefer to stay in Jagatsinghpur.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport to Jagatsinghpur is situated in Bhubaneswar, the Biju Patnaik Airport at a distance of 44 kms. This airport has connectivity to all the major cities and towns of India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Jagatsinghpur does have a railway station. But people prefer to come to this place either through Bhubaneswar or Cuttack. The Cuttack Railway Station is the major railhead to this port town which is located 60 kms away.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Jagatsinghpur can be reached via road transport. National highway 5 links Jagatsinghpur to others parts of Odisha. As a result, the place is accessible from all the major cities and towns in Odisha.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(406, 14, 31, 752, 'Rajasthan', 'INDIA', 'JAJPUR', 'highway-332365_640.jpg', 'highway-332365_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Jajpur is a historic place of pilgrimage is located at a distance of 92 kms from Cuttack. Once upon a time Jajpur was the capital of Kalinga kingdom and had achieved the pinnacle of glory in archeological excellence. Jajpur is honoured for its natural resources, mines and industries. Situated on the bank of river Baitarani it has the sacred shrine of Goddess Biraja, Sveta Baraha, Sapta Matruka and a host of other shrines. It is famous for Saktipitha of Goddess Biraja. It is a great pilgrimage destination as the district is dotted with a number of temples, each having a different story to tell. Situated on the right bank of river Baitarani, Jajpur is said to be named after Somavanshi king &lsquo;Jajata Kesari&rsquo; of the early tenth century. Also, as this place is dedicated mainly to the Hindu deity Viraja Khetra, the history of this place is closely associated to the legend. It was believed by Archaeologists that this city, being a symbol of ancient Hindu culture, was once in the history, filled with scores of highly rich ancient Hindu temples like the nearby temple town Bhubaneswar. In 736 AD, there was an event occurred with the entry of the Bhaumakaras. The Bhaumas and Somvanshi are the two most powerful dynasties that ruled over the Odisha wholly for about a long period of four centuries and are also creditable for the culture developed in this state during their reign. During the King Somvanshi&rsquo;s reign, he made Jajpur his capital and this is the reason behind the development of flourished states of Odisha because Jajpur contributed a lot in the smooth transformation of the other states during the King Somvanshi&rsquo;s rule.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Being a well liked and often visited tourist place of Odisha essential staying facilities in Jajpur is provided by various hotels and lodges spreads across the region. There are several hotels ranging from luxury to budget. These facilities offered are 24 hours room service, free Wi-Fi and in house laundry and so on.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport to Jajpur is Biju Patnaik Airport, bhubaneshwar which is 86 kms away from Jajpur city centre.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - The nearest railway station to Jajpur is Bhadrakh Railway Station which is 30 kms away from Jajpur city centre.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Bus</strong> - Instead of Jajpur tourists can a get a bus to Chandikhol which is at a distance of 26 kms from Jajpur, on regular basis.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - JAJPUR - [FAMOUS FOR PAKHALA BHATA]<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(407, 14, 31, 1658, 'Odisha', 'INDIA', 'JHARSUGUDA', 'india-1034833_640.jpg', 'india-1034833_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The district of Jharsuguda came into existence on April 1, 1994. The district covers an area of 2203 sq kms. Out of the 30 districts of Odisha, Jharsuguda is considered to be the one that is rich in mines, industries &amp; business. Jharsuguda Town is the head quarters of the district. Widely known as the Power house of Orissa due to the presence of a large number of thermal power plants in the nearby region, Jharsuguda is located in the state of Orissa and is also the administrative headquarters of the Jharsuguda district. Jharsuguda is regarded as an upcoming industrial centre, primarily in the metal and cement sectors. Jharsuguda City Guide is incomplete without a mention of its industrial prowess. In current years, Jharsuguda district has observed a large scale Industrialization and is growing rapidly on a higher level. As per the legend, the farmers from Jharkhand state established Jharsuguda during 12th Century AD. In 1936 under the British rule, Jharsuguda became a part of Sambalpur district. Jharsuguda district has a rich and developed cultural heritage.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">A good number of small, affordable and large size hotels, Pantha Nivas &amp; other staying facilities are available in the district. Jharsuguda has some medium to budget accommodation options. The hotels are homely and laced with the modern amenities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Jharsuguda has its own Domestic Airport named as Jharsuguda Airport. It is well connected to a spectrum of cities in the country. The nearest International Airport is Swami Vivekanand Airport Raipur, roughly 312 kms from Jharsuguda.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Jharsuguda has its own Railway Station named as Jharsuguda Railway Junction which is connected to the major cities of Odisha. It is linked with the cities like New Delhi, Bangalore, Howrah, Mumbai, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Jharsuguda is connected to the major towns of the state by SH 10 and NH 42. By buses or taxis one can reach Jharsuguda easily.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - TIWARI SWEETS, AT STATION ROAD, JHARSHUGADA - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;DOSA, BADA, SAMOSA, KACHORI AND GAJAR KA HALWA]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - ANNA IDLY HOTEL, BUS STAND, JHARSHUGADA - [FAMOUS FOR SOUTH INDIAN DISHES]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - JHARSUGUDA - [FAMOUS FOR MATHAPULI( IS A DESERT MADE FROM URAD DAL AND SUGAR SYRUP), &nbsp;SANTULA IS A DISH MADE WITH VEGETABLES]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(408, 14, 31, 1658, 'Odisha', 'INDIA', 'KALAHANDI', 'forest-597405_640.jpg', 'forest-597405_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kalahandi is a district in Odisha rich in history and culture. Located on the confluence of the rivers Uttei and Tel, Kalahandi is a home to some very ancient temples of extensive architectural excellence dating back to 12th Century. Many picturesque hills along with cascading waterfalls add to the beauty of the town. Several archaeological evidences dating back to Stone Age and Iron Age were found here. The Kalahandi Utsav is celebrated every year and showcases fine art, culture, music and handicrafts which is famous worldwide. Kalahandi tourism offers its visitors some exotic locations of interesting history and exquisite natural beauty. Asurgarh is a place where traces of human settlement of 2000 years ago could be found. Gudahandi is a hill that marvels some ancient paintings inside its caves. Rabandarh is a beautiful waterfall whereas Mohangiri is home to an ancient Shiva Temple with some scenic natural beauty. The Lal Bahadur Shashtri Stadium is also located here where various sports and fairs are organized. Kalahandi is well connected with all the major cities of Odisha. The best time to visit Kalahandi is during the monsoon season.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are a number of budget hotels to stay in and around the city of Kalahandi. Since a huge number of tourists come to visit this place each year, there are good accommodation facilities available for these visitors. Along with the number of budget hotels, there are also quite a few luxury hotels available nearby this region which adds to the comfort of the tourists.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - One can travel to Kalahandi by air either from the Raipur Airport which is 259 kms away or from the Vishakapatnam airport which is 341 kms away. The Bhubaneswar airport which is 450 kms away is another option.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The Kesinga Railway Station is the nearest railway station which lies in close vicinity to Kalahandi. It is well connected to all the major cities of India including Mumbai, Delhi, Bangalore, Kolkata and Chennai.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Two major National Highway 201 and 217 pass through Kalahandi. Many state run buses are readily available which connects all the major cities like Bhubaneswar, Cuttack and Sambalpur etc. Several private buses are also available.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - A number of private vehicles like bikes and cars can be seen in the roads of the city. Other people use the public means of transport like buses, autos, taxis, etc. In relatively smaller areas, hands pulled rickshaws are also used for the purpose of travelling. Autos are a common mode for transport in this region. Apart from this, one can also hire private vehicles for the travel agencies for sightseeing purposes and exploring the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - SHREE BALAJI SWEETS, Near MANIKESHWARI TEMPLE, BHAWANIPATNA - [FAMOUS FOR VARITIES OF BISCUITS, CAKE AND ICECREAM]<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(409, 14, 31, 1658, 'Odisha', 'INDIA', 'KANDHAMAL', 'hill-828846_640.jpg', 'hill-828846_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kandhamal is among the most attractive tourist destinations of Odisha. Adorned with natural beauty and bounties and inhabited by indigenous tribes, this place is the home to some typical tribal population. Kandhamal tourism showcases to its visitors the vast coffee plantation which has crept on the body of towering mountain named Daringbadi. Kandhamal attracts many visitors to marvel the handmade articles of cane, Dokra, terracotta and bamboo. Kandhamal is flanked by many tourist hotspots which attracts many nature enthusiasts all year round. The cascading waterfalls like Patudi Waterfall, Ludu Waterfall, Katramal and Pakadadarah Waterfall invites many people from nearby and far off places to marvel the beauty. The village of Chakapada is ready to surprise the visitors with its unique Shiva Temple and the trees inside the temple premises which lean towards south. Born out of the confluence of two hills, the Balaskumpa village is a scenic site to marvel. Inhabited by local tribes that dwell into the dense and impenetrable forests which also shelter some wild animals, Belghar is among the exotic locations of Kandhamal. The best time to visit Kandhamal is from September to May.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\nThere are a number of hotels available in Kandhamal for a good stay. Most of the Kandhamal hotels are located either at scenic points away from the crowded places inclusive all room facilities that make vacation holidays more memorable.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport to Kandhamal is the Bhubaneswar airport which is 211 kms from Kandhamal. A small airstrip is present at Gudari which is 5 kms from Phulbani which serves as a landing ground for small planes and helicopters.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The nearest railhead is Rairakhol of Sambalpur district. However, the closest major railway station to Kandhamal is Behrampur which is 165 kms from Phulbani.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Kandhamal can be approached from Bhubaneswar, Sambalpur and Behrampur by road. Sometimes the road may turn out to be bumpy and rough but the panoramic view of nature while passing through these roads are breathtaking and enchanting. Several state run buses from Bhubaneswar, Sambalpur and Behrampur connect one to Phulbani.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - KUNA FAST FOOD CENTER, LOCATED AT DARINGBADI - (FAMOUS FOR CHIKEN POKORA AND MUTTON SOUP)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - ANNAPURNA RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT NATIONAL HIGHWAY 217, BHANJANAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN CHILLI, BUTTER NAAN AND KABAB)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '');
INSERT INTO `city` (`id`, `continent_id`, `country_id`, `state_id`, `state_name`, `country_name`, `ci_name`, `main_image`, `main_image1`, `description`, `accomdation`, `transportation`, `eatable`, `experience_type_id`) VALUES
(410, 14, 31, 1658, 'Odisha', 'INDIA', 'KENDRAPARA', 'sunset-317657_640.jpg', 'sunset-317657_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kendrapara district was carved out of the erstwhile district of Cuttack Kendrapara district is situated in Central Coastal plain zone of Odisha. The district is bounded by Bhadrak district at its North, Jagatsinghpur district at its South, Cuttack district at its west and Bay of Bengal at its East. There are various tourist places or picnic spots in Kendrapara district of Odisha. Where tourists can enjoy a lot and also it is the great place for the nature lovers because there are so many natural beauty picnic spots in Kendrapara. It is a great place for the nature lovers. If planning for a winter picnic trip then the best place is Kendrapara. There are many tourist places in Kendrapara District. Batighara is the first lighthouse installed in eastern coast of India. It is surrounded with pleasant natural beauty. In front of the Batighar, False Point Port was the first modern port of the Odisha coast. This port was commissioned in the year 1855. Kanika Palace is one of the most popular tourist places in Kendrapara District. It is situated in Rajkanika block and around 50 kms from Kendrapara. The beauty of the palace is unbelievable. Aul Palace is another tourist site and it is an ancient palace spread over 40 acres of land. Kudanagari is an ancient centre of maritime business, which is situated in Patkura constituency. A massive sand dune sprawling over 15 acres of land and of a height 25 feet, surrounded by deep forest is a popular pilgrim centre.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kendrapara has some deluxe and a lot of medium and budget accommodation options. There are hotels with all facilities to make the stay a memorable one.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport to Kendraparha is Biju Patnaik Airport, Bhubaneshwar which is 68 kms away from Kendraparha city centre.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The nearest railway station to Kendraparha is Dashrathpur Railway Station which is 37 kms away from Kendraparha city centre.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Kendrapara is just about 75 kilometres from the state capital, Bhubaneswar. To reach Kendrapara one can go via Cuttack Jagatpur Salipur state highway or on the National Highway 5 and 5 A crossing at Chandikhol towards Paradip.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - KENDRAPARA - (FAMOUS FOR RASABALI IS A SWEET DISH &nbsp;SOAKED IN THICK FLAVOURED MILK AND GARNISHED WITH CARDAMOMS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - HOTEL PARADISE, LOCATED AT NEAR PETROL PUMP,COLLEGE CHAKA - (FAMOUS FOR MUTTON CURRY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - VIJAY PANDA CHOWMIN CENTER, LOCATED AT 21, MAIN ROAD, BALAGANDI BAZAR - {FAMOUS FOR CHOWMIN, EGG ROLLS, CHICKEN ROLLS, CHICKEN BALLS (PAKODAS), CHILLI CHICKEN}</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(411, 14, 31, 1658, 'Odisha', 'INDIA', 'KENDUJHAR (KEONJHAR)', 'panchgani-1650030_6402.jpg', 'panchgani-1650030_6403.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Keonjhar is a beautiful place situated on the northern fringes of Orissa. It is one of the largest districts in the state and it is also a municipality. The district is surrounded by the state of Jharkhand in its north and the three districts of Jajpur, Dhenkanal and Mayurbhanj in the south, west and east respectively. There is the famous Keonjhar Plateau from which the Baitarani River originates. Keonjhar tourism attracts a lot of visitors all year around. The place is abundant in flora and fauna as well as in the occurrence of minerals and ores. The place has some picturesque cascading waterfalls to boast too. Keonjhar is the only district in the state that has so much diversified natural resources. More than one third of the district is covered with dense forests and there is a rich source of manganese ore found in many parts of the district. The Rebana and the Kalapata blocks of the district are the places where tigers are found. Keonjhar tourism offers a lot of attractions to its visitors. The places of tourist interest are the Kandadhar Waterfalls, Sanghagara Waterfalls and Bada Ghagara Waterfalls. Hundreds of visitors come to see these waterfalls. The temple at Ghatagaon is another hotspot. November is the month that is preferred by many to visit Keonjhar as it is the time when the weather condition is moderate.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are a number of Hotels in Keonjhar. From Luxury hotels to the Budget hotels, it offers excellent accommodation in Keonjhar. The Hotels in Keonjhar offers lavishly designed and well furnished rooms. Hotel offers tourists an ideal retreat and excellent business amenities to the corporate as well. The hotels offer lavishly designed and well furnished rooms which are spacious and affordable as well.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Biju Pattanaik Airport in Bhubaneswar is the closest airport to reach Keonjhar. The place is located at a distance of 269 kms away from the Bhubaneswar Airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - To reach Keonjhar by rail, one has to go to the J.K Road railhead which is at a distance of 114 kms. The railway station is connected well with the other parts of the state and it takes just two hours to reach Keonjhar from the railway station.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Keonjhar is a very well connected place. It is connected with all the major towns and cities of the state. The National Highway 15 bisects the district and one can find private cars, buses to reach the place safely without any problems.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - It is very easy to travel within Keonjhar. There are all sorts of buses, autos and cabs available in the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SWAD RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT GANDHI CHOWK&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;- (FAMOUS FOR LACHA PARATHA AND BUTTER PANEER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - SURAJ RESTAURANT &amp; BAKERY,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT NATIONAL HIGHWAY 215 - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;CAKE AND SNACKS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - CHINA FAST FOOD, LOCATED IN KEONJHAR - (FAMOUS FOR TANDOORI CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - SAHU, LOCATED IN KEONJHAR - (&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;FAMOUS FOR DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - KENDUJHAR - (&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;FAMOUS FOR BADI IS A SNACK MADE FROM BLACK-GRAM)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(412, 14, 31, 1658, 'Odisha', 'INDIA', 'KORAPUT', 'signal-post-179265_640.jpg', 'signal-post-179265_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">If one&rsquo;s desire is to marvel at the awesome power of nature, Koraput is the place to be. The district&rsquo;s main claims to fame are enchanting hills, verdant forests, winding streams and exotic wildlife and a rich tribal way of life. The commercial nerve centre of Koraput district, Jeypore is bounded by hills of the Eastern Ghats and Araku hills on three sides and has also an impressive collection of architectural sights. Untainted by commercial tourist development, Koraput is a tourist&rsquo;s destination for solitude seekers, wildlife lovers and history buffs. Jeypore is the convenient base for exploring the places of interest in and around. The district of Koraput derives its name from its headquarters the present town of Koraput. In ancient times when the Nalas were ruling over this tract, Pushkari near modern Umarkot was the capital city. In the medieval period Nandapur developed as the capital under the Silavamsi kings and sometimes under the kings of the Solaar dynasty. Vikram Dev of the Solaar dynasty shifted his headquarters to Jeypore about the middle of the 17th century and this town prospered as the capital. Koraput was chosen by the British in 1870 for better health prospects.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Accommodation in Koraput is abundant with an assortment of hotels and guest houses to go with every budget and every experience. The accommodation in the city is appropriate for the budget minded tourists and can vary from simple rooms to well furnished rooms. From hotels to lodge one can find everything that can make the stay enjoyable.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><br />\r\n<strong>By Air </strong>- The Visakhapatnam is the closest airport to Koraput, which is at a distance of 133 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - Koraput has its own junction named as Koraput Railway station that connects it to nearby foremost places.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Bus</strong> - OSRTC buses are regularly plied from all parts of Orissa state to access the Koraput.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Koraput has good connectivity with other parts of the state as well as some major cities of neighbouring states, by means of road network. NH 43 passes through Koraput.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - KORAPUT - [FAMOUS FOR PANASA MANJI BHAJA ARE JACJFRUIT SEEDS ARE FRIED AND SEASONED IN JAGGERY(GUDA) ; JHATA MANJI ALU TIANA ARE INDIAN BEANS CURRY WITH POTATOES ; MANDIA IS A SOUP MADE OF STALE BOILED RICE WATER AND MANDIA POWDER]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(413, 14, 31, 1658, 'Odisha', 'INDIA', 'MALKANGIRI', 'hillside-983954_640.jpg', 'hillside-983954_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">One of the newly created districts of Odisha, Malkangiri derives its name from Malyabantagiri described in several ancient texts. Set amidst green hills, the place is endowed with stunning beauty and unspoilt elegance. The expanse of wilderness and awe inspiring landscapes offer some of the most exciting travel opportunities. The colourful tribes and their unexplored cultural heritage provide tourists food for thought. Malkangiri has an undeniable charm and the other attractions in the districts are first ports of call for the travellers. It is no surprise that this place is fast emerging as a travel destination of top order. The district is named after its headquarters town Malkangiri. During formation of Odisha Province in 1936 Malkangiri was a &ldquo;Taluk&rdquo; of Nabrangpur sub division of Koraput district of Odisha. In 1962 it was upgraded to a subdivision of Koraput District. The present Malkangiri got its identity as an independent district due to reorganisation of districts of Odisha with effect from October 2nd 1992. During the reign of Lord Ramachandra, Malkangiri occupied an important place in the entire &ldquo;Ramayana&rdquo;. It was the holy river &ldquo;The Tamasa&rdquo; and its environs which encouraged Saint Balmiki to express his internal feelings in the form of The Ramayana, the holiest book of Hindus. This place was known as &ldquo;Malyavantagiri&rdquo; in the Ramayana. River the Tamasa flowing out of a cave has derived its name from a tribal word &ldquo;Tansa&rdquo;, which means cave. The scenic beauty if this Malyavantagiri has found an important place in the &ldquo;Dandi Ramayana&rdquo; of Balaram Das.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Malkangiri is a fast developing region of Odisha. Though most of the areas are inhabited and looked after by tribes, but still there are some hotels where tourists can opt to stay while travelling to this rustic place of Odisha. There are many local shops and street side small food stores that offer local food and snacks. Most of the hotels are equipped with basic amenities and are known for serving visitors for decades.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Malkangiri is connected by good motor able roads to different places in India. Malkangiri is 380 kms from Visakhapatnam and 630 kms from Bhubaneswar. There are regular interstate bus services from the nearby towns and cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- The nearest Railway station is Koraput Junction connecting several important cities in India.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest Airport is Visakhapatnam connected by regular flights with different cites of India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Taxis, auto rickshaws, cycle rickshaws and local bus services are available. Autos are also a main source of transport. Tourist taxis and deluxe buses are available on rent from travel services.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - Q9 RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT MALKANGIRI - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN BIRYANI)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(414, 14, 31, 1658, 'Odisha', 'INDIA', 'NABARANGPUR', 'india-380051_640.jpg', 'india-380051_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Nabarangpur until recently called as Nowrangpur. A part of erstwhile Koraput District ruled by the Solar Dynasty of Jeypore in the past was a grant received from the Maharaja of Jeypore in the year 1820 AD. Nabarangpur District was inaugurated on 2nd October 1992. Though Koraput was vivisected into four parts, each segment enjoys the status of newly formed district. The inhabitants here are mostly tribals, nomadic and almost aboriginal. Encounter with the civilized population in the township has changed their lifestyle to some extent by a few of them like Paraja, Kondhas, Gadava still live the primitive life style. They mostly depend on cultivation and forest products. Some speak Oriya in a corrupt form, difficult for the chaste Oriya speaking people to understand. They are an admixture of several words and phrases from aboriginal dialects. Boarder areas have a heavy dose of Chhattisgarhi language in the west and of Kalahandi dialect in the north. The religion of the district is composite. The history of Nabarangpur is inextricably interlinked with that of Koraput District. In a sense, its language, style of living, heritage, geographical location flora and fauna and even climate is not distinct from the rest of the component of Koraput district. Its boundary stretches in the north to Kalahandi district west to Jagadalpur district in Chatishgarh, east to Kalahandi and Rayagada and south to Koraput district with the river Indravati separating the two districts.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">There is no dearth of quality hotels and lodges for those looking for accommodation options in Nabarangpur. With the latest technology and a wide variety of services, these hotels offer homely ambience and a memorable stay for the visitors.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport is at Visakhapatnam, 300 kms away from Nabarangpur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train </strong>- Tourists can reach through Koraput 66 kms away or Rayagada 175 kms away from Nabarangpur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - From Bhubaneswar, one can go to Nabarangpur either through Phulbani and Bhawanipatna or through Berhampur and Ganjam. The road is very scenic.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(415, 14, 31, 1658, 'Odisha', 'INDIA', 'NAYAGARH', 'road-sign-253211_640.jpg', 'road-sign-253211_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">An administrative district of Odisha, Nayagarh district was created in 1st April 1993 when the erstwhile Puri district was split into three distinct districts. The district is bounded by Cuttack district on the North, Kandhamal district on the West, Ganjam district on the South and Khordha district on its East. Birth history of Nayagarh district in around the 13th century and is considered as an important part in the political history of Odisha. King Suryamani of Baghela dynasty came to Puri on a pilgrimage from Madhya Pradesh and established his kingdom at Nayagarh. Nayagarh district consists of the four Garjat states of ex-states Ranpur, Nayagarh, Khandapara and Daspalla. The aboriginal Savaras and Kandhas are the indigenous people of Nayagarh district. The district experiences tropical climate, with the summers being hot and the winter&rsquo;s cold. Rainfall is generally heavy during the monsoons, which occur during the months of July and August. South West monsoon is primarily responsible for the rainfall in this district. Nayagarh district is the land of eminent personalities. The district of Nayagarh celebrates many fairs and festivals round the year. Nayagarh is well irrigated with number of rivers flowing through it. Mahanadi flows in this district forming beautiful gorge of Satkosia. Similarly river Brutanga a tributary of river Mahanadi that rises from the hilly areas of Phulbani and Bhanjanagar carries large volumes of water to the river Mahanadi. This district is situated in the hilly ranges in the West and its North Eastern parts has formed a small well cultivated fertile valleys intersected by small streams.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">As at other places of the State, the facility for staying like, lodging and accommodations available are not of very high standards, but good and affordable hotels can be obtained. The range of hotels and food facilities available at Nayagarh is always suitable for all classes of peoples and travellers.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - There are no regular flights from other major cities of the country to Nayagarh. The nearest airport is Bhubaneswar, which is at a distance of 82 kms from Nayagarh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Nayagarh Railway Station is well connected to other major cities of the country via regular trains.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Instead of Nayagarh tourists can a get a bus to Barbil on regular basis. State transport and private buses ply between Bhubaneswar and Nayagarh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong>- 82 kms from Bhubaneswar and 67 kms from Khurda Town, Nayagarh are on National Highway 224, frequented by regular bus services from Bhubaneswar, Balangir and other places.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - BASUDEV DHABA, LOCATED AT NH16, CHANDPUR - (FAMOUS FOR CHILLY CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - NAYAGARH - (FAMOUS FOR CHHENA PODA &nbsp;IS A CHEESE DESSERT MADE FROM CHHENA CHEESE, SUGAR, CASHEW NUTS AND RAISINS)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(416, 14, 31, 1658, 'Odisha', 'INDIA', 'NUAPADA', 'sunset-208206_640.jpg', 'sunset-208206_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">The District Nuapada came into existence on April 1, 1993, by carving out of undivided Kalahandi district. The district covers a total geographical area of 3408 sq kms with its administrative headquarters located at Nuapada. The rank of the district is 19th in the state with reference to area. Its boundaries extend in the North, West and south to Raipur district in Madhya Pradesh and in the East to Bargarh, Balangir and Kalahandi districts. The plains of Naupada subdivision fringed by rugged hill ranges stretch southward, which belong to the main line of the Eastern Ghats and contains extensive plateaus of about 1200 mts in elevation with long tropical grass grown over them. They contain mineral deposits such as laterite, graphite and bauxite. The hill sides rising up precipitously from the plains are covered with dense sal forests.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Major accommodation facilities are available at Nuapada. A number of good hotels are also available at many places of the district.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Train</strong> - Nuapada is the nearest railway junction from the district headquarter town Nuapada that is located at a distance of 3 kms. Most of the express train stop at Khariar Road located at a distance of 10 kms from Nuapada.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Road</strong> - The district is very well connected by roadways. It is connected with NH 217 and SH 3.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest Airport is Swami Vivekananda Airport at Raipur, Chhattisgarh, that is located at a distance of 120 kms from Nuapada.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(417, 14, 31, 1658, 'Odisha', 'INDIA', 'RAYAGADA', 'munnar-1639120_6402.jpg', 'munnar-1639120_6403.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">About 95 kms north of Jeypore, Rayagada, the headquarters town of the district, is a land of green forests, beautiful meadows, stunning waterfalls, terraced valleys, rich tribal life and culture. It is also an industrial town with a large scale Ferro-manganese factory, a sugar and a paper mill. The town is famous for a temple dedicated to Majhighariani. The place casts a spell on the visitors and is starting point for other important places of interest of the district. Besides, on the immediate outskirts of the township, the visitor encounters colourful indigenous tribal people in their natural habitat. In the third century BC, during the reign of Ashoka the Great, it was under Kalinga Empire. The hilly track between Bansadhara and Nagabali was famous for spices. The Rastriks were defeated by Kharvela, the only Aryan Emperor of Kalinga, during the Chawpagada battle. During the English regime, Rayagada came under Jeypore administration and later was part of Koraput District. As part of the extension plan of districts in the Orissa state, on 2nd October 1992 Rayagda District was carved out of the erstwhile Koraput district.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The hotel industry in Rayagada has prominent presence. Keeping the tourism focused, Rayagada has many hotels in the surrounding area. Few of the hotels are real good and offer great service. The accommodation and eating can be a good experience at this place. The Odisha cuisine and the wonderful location give the tourist an amazing experience in the hotel.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- The city is well connected by the road as well. The NH 43 is almost 100 kms away from the city. However, it does not separate out the city from well road connectivity. Daily bus services to major nearby cities like Cuttack, Bhubaneshwar, Vishakhapatnam and others are frequent and comfortable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Rayagada has its own railway station is a directly connected to the major cities of India. Nearest cities like Raipur, Bokaro, Nagpur is also well connected by the Indian Railways.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- When it comes to Airways, the city does not have a dedicated airport. However, the nearest airport Vishakhapatnam serves the city well. The city is located at proximity and people coming from Vishakhapatnam airport can reach the Rayagada city very comfortably.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- There are dedicated bus terminus and bus services which make the transportation of the city of high standard.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - SADGURU, SWAGAT HOTEL LN, NEW COLONY - [FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN CHILLI AND MUTTON CURRY]<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(418, 14, 31, 1658, 'Odisha', 'INDIA', 'SAMBALPUR', 'hill-road-204115_640.jpg', 'hill-road-204115_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Sambalpur is an amalgamation of history and modernity. The land that is today known as Sambalpur has seen many divisions and mergers under the aegis of numerous rulers and governments. The cultural traces that the different governing bodies left behind has led to a potpourri of historic experiences that has shaped the current day Sambalpur. As it stands today in the western hemisphere of Odisha the district is a culturally rich, abundantly lush landscape with warm welcoming people. Centuries ago Sambalpur was renowned for its diamonds it was a hub in the diamond trade route. The diamonds obtained in and around the Mahanadi River are coveted by numerous collectors and enthusiasts today as they are believed to be amidst the best diamonds in terms of clarity in the world. A colourless 146 carat diamond called &lsquo;Taj-i-Mah&rsquo; literally translates into crown of the moon found in Sambalpur stands testimony to the purity of the diamonds found in the area. The traditional costume for women, the Sambalpuri sari, is a beautiful creation unique to the area. Tourism in Sambalpur is sustained for various reasons. The climate of Sambalpur is broadly divided into summer, monsoon and winter, where the summers are humid and winters are nippy. With the unique sights, sounds, tastes and experiences that Sambalpur has to offer, it is no surprise then that it is a tourist&rsquo;s paradise. The best time to visit Sambalpur is between the months of September and March.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are several hotels and accommodation facilities available in the city. There are many options available for a comfortable stay well matching the convenience and budget. Minimum tariff is from Rs 100 and maximum is Rs 2500 approximately.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - There is an airport which is under construction as of now in Jharsugada 50 kms from Sambalpur. So, till that airport is fully functional, there is Swami Vivekananda Airport Raipur which is 262 kms from Sambalpur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Sambalpur has four railway stations, namely Sambalpur khetrajpur, Sambalpur road fatak, Hirakud, Sambalpur city. These railway stations are well connected to all major metro cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Roads in Sambalpur are well connected with nearby cities. Rourkela Sambalpur State Highway 10 is under construction to transform this from a two lane highway to a four or even six lane highway. There are buses leaving in every fifteen minutes to Jharsuguda and Bargarh from the terminal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport-</strong> City buses have recently been launched in this city to enhance and improve the state of local transportation. Till date, the local transport modes in this city were rickshaws or cycle rickshaws. The frequency and comfort provided by city buses have made it an interesting inclusion in the feature of local transport.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SAMBALPUR - [FAMOUS FOR AAMISA JHOL AND JHURI BHAJA IS A NON-VEGATARIAN DISH]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - KEDIA&#39;S, OPPOSITE ICICI BANNK, BUDHARAJA ROAD - [FAMOUS FOR GREEN DAL AND RAITA]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - THE PUNJABI GRILL, &nbsp;V.S.S. MARG - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;CHICHEN AND CRISPY CHILLY BABY CORN]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - SONU FAST FOOD, LOCATED AT SAKHIPARA - (FAMOUS FOR ROASTED CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - CHAT BHANDAR, LOCATED AT GOLBAZAR, PATTNAYAKPADA - (FAMOUS FOR CHAT ITEMS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - SAMLESWARI, LOCATED AT KHETRAJPUR - (FAMOUS FOR EGGPLANT(BRINJAL) CURRY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - SAMBALPUR - (FAMOUS FOR PANASA TARKARI IS A DISH MADE FROM UNRIPE JACKFRUIT AND MIXED WITH ONIONS AND POTATO)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>8 - BAY LEAF, LOCATED AT BUDHARAJA ROAD, SAKHIPARA - (FAMOUS FOR BIRYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>9 - AMAZING BAKERY, LOCATED AT SAHEZ PLAZA, GAIETY ROAD, GOLEBAZAR - (FAMOUS FOR CAKES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>10 - PIPLANI SWEETS, LOCATED AT NEAR GOLE BAZAR, LAXMI TALKIES ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR DHOKLA)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(419, 14, 31, 732, 'Andhra Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'NELLORE (SRI POTTI SRI RAMULU)', 'mountains-1643627_6404.jpg', 'mountains-1643627_6405.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">A very beautiful city, having colossal historical significance, Nellore is incredibly famous for its religious and spiritual legacy. It is located in the state of Andhra Pradesh and is the administrative headquarters of Sri Potti Sri Ramulu Nellore district. Nellore city guide is full of references to the interesting spots. The several interesting places like Kamahshi Amavari Temple, Jonnavada, Golgamundi Venkaya Swamy Temple and Rajarajesjwari Temple etc. are worth visiting in the city. Nellore had been under the reign of Maurya Dynasty, Kharavela of Chedi Dynasty and Eastern Ganga of Kalinga Empire, Satavahanas, Pallavas, Kakatiyas, Cholas, Telugu Cholas and Pandyas and thus still bears the souvenirs of their influence. Nellore is majorly known for the production of various ores such as mica and lime and is also famous for the production of rice. The city is much admired for aquaculture and is one of the fastest growing cities in the state. It is also famous for its delicious sweets like malai kajaa and a real Andhra sweet, the bobbatlu. The district was formerly known as Nellore itself. It is home to various prominent temples and is a significant agricultural centre. Nellore city is located on the banks of the River Penna, and a wide variety of crops are grown in the region. It is of critical importance as far as trade and commerce is concerned, as it is situated on the main road that connects Vijayawada and the capital city of Tamil Nadu, Chennai.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Nellore offers a wide range of accommodations options ranging from budget and medium hotels to luxury hotels. Apart from picturesque views, tourists may expect good hospitality, efficient staff and impressive food as well. Hotel Abhiram, Hotel Leo and Hotel Yash Park are few of the highly rated hotels in the area.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Choosing to travel by air is a good decision in terms of saving time and having a comfortable journey. The nearest airport to the city is the Tirupati Airport, which is about 103 kilometres south west but its connectivity to Tirupati airport is limited to Hyderabad, Vishakhapatnam and other cities in Andhra Pradesh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - There are many buses connecting Nellore from Chennai and Hyderabad. The 2 main bus stations available are: PSR Bus Station and RTC Bus Stand. There are many private luxury bus services available to connect Hyderabad and Chennai from the Railway station area. Buses of Tamil Nadu state road transport corporations start from Madras bus stand very close to the RTC bus stand and they operate mainly to Chennai.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Nellore has good train services from cities like Chennai, Hyderabad and other places in Andhra Pradesh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Nellore has a good connectivity of bus services by the APSRTC for intra and intercity, both being good for travel purposes. Intra city buses function in many major cities of Andhra Pradesh which will help to explore the all around the place. Tourists may also hire a taxi if convenience and fast travelling is the main aim.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - BABU, LOCATED AT GRAND TRUNK ROAD, RAMJI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR ICE CREAM, FRUITJUICE AND VARITIES OF DESERT)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - MURALIKRISHNA GHEE SWEETS, LOCATED AT GRAND TRUNK ROAD, RAMESH REDDY NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR MALAI KAJA IS A SWEET AND KAJU FRY IS A SNACK)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - KARAM, LOCATED AT RAMJI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - SALMA BIRYANI, LOCATED AT MASJID CENTER, BALAJI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN PAKODA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - SAI BABA FOOD CORNER, LOCATED AT NEAR LEELA MAHAL, BESIDE BSNL OFFICE - (FAMOUS FOR MANCHURIAN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - NELLORE - {FAMOUS FOR CHEPALA PULUSU (MALABAR MATTHI CURRY) IS A CURRY MADE FROM SARDINES, &nbsp;VEGETABLES (OKRA OR ONIONS) RICE, BREAD}</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(420, 14, 31, 732, 'Andhra Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'ANANTAPUR', 'temple-183745_1280.jpg', 'temple-183745_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Anantapur is a city and the headquarters of the Anantapur district in Andhra Pradesh. This is the largest district in the state bounded on north by Kurnool, on the east by Kadapa and Chittoor and on the south and west by the Karnataka State. This is also one of the famous Andhra Pradesh tourist places. This region is also known by the name of Anantapuram and was earlier known as Anantasagaram, which means an endless ocean. The villages of Anantasagaram and Bukkarayasamudram were constructed by Chilkkavodeya, the minister of Bukka-I, a Vijayanagar ruler. During the Vijaynagar period, Anantapur was an important center and popularly known as Hande Anantapuram. Anantapur and a couple of other places were gifted by the Vijaynagar rulers to Hanumappa Naidu of the Hande family. Penukonda in Ananthapur district was the capital was Vijayanagaras after the fall of Hampi. Anantapur is home to many ancient temples, monuments and forts that give a glimpse into the rich history of the region. Lepakshi is renowned for grand architecture and repository of mural paintings of the Vijayanagar Kings. Puttaparthi, Kadiri Lakshmi Narasimha Swamy Temple famous for the idol sweating, Chintala Venkataramana Swamy Temple and Bugga Ramalingheswara Swamy Temple in Tadipatri some of the well known tourist spots in the district. The region is also well known for its booming silk and cotton weaving industry in Dharmavaram. Penukonda Fort, Hemavathi, Rayadurgam fort and Gooty fort are the other attractions here. The summer is very hot here and it&#39;s cool only during winter season. Best time to visit the town is between September and February.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Anantapur is an important city of Andhra Pradesh. It is a popular tourist attraction and each year thousands of tourists visit Anantapur and regions around it. Thus, to cater to the increasing demands of travellers, the hospitality industry has undergone and remarkable change. Over the past few years a lot of resorts and hotels have come up in different parts of Anantapur. Tourists can choose the accommodation as per their choice and budget. Anantapur has a perfect mix of 3 star hotels, luxury hotels, budget hotels and lodges.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air </strong>- The closest airport is Sri Satya Sai Airport in Puttaparthi. And the closest International airport is Bangalore which is at a distance of nearly 119 kms from Anantapur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Train</strong> - The closest junction is Sri Satya Sai Prasanthi Nilayam railway station in Puttaparthi, which links it to major cities of India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Road</strong> - Anantapur is well connected via road network to all foremost cities in Andhra Pradesh. Anantapur is connected by NH 7 and NH 205 from all major cities throughout India.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Bus</strong> - APSRTC buses connect Anantapur with all other foremost cities in Andhra Pradesh. There are plenty of buses to Anantapur from Hyderabad&#39;s main bus terminals.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(421, 14, 31, 732, 'Andhra Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'CHITTOOR', 'sunset-850877_6401.jpg', 'sunset-850877_6402.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Chittoor is a town and the head quarters of the Chittoor District in the State of Andhra Pradesh. It is located on the Renigunta Katipadi railway line and on the National Highway between Chennai and Bangalore. Chittoor is also termed as the Temple Town of Tirumala and Tirupati, one of the major pilgrim centres in the entire country. The town is regarded as the gateway to most of the pilgrims coming to visit Tirupati from South Indian states like Karnataka, Kerala and Tamilnadu. The climate here is moderate with tolerable summer and good rains. Best time to visit Chittoor is between September and February. The warm and friendly people of the town are welcoming and make the visitor feel comfortable. Steeped in religion, devotion and architecture, Chittoor is a place that everyone should visit at least once in their lifetime. Also blessed with scenic beauty, cascading waterfalls and a beautiful hill station, Chittoor is not a disappointment to the traveller who seeks redemption from the busy metro life. Also known as the Mango City, Chittoor offers myriad varieties of heavenly mangoes to please its visitors. Situated in the valley of the Ponni River, Chittoor is a market for grain, sugarcane, and peanuts. Its industries include oilseed and rice milling. Jaggery from Aragonda area, a small town near Chittor is famous throughout the country. Chittor is a major place for producing hatcheries and mangoes.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Chittoor as a city and a district as a whole is one of the most visited places in Andhra Pradesh. With the increase in the volume of tourists, the hospitality industry has also received a good boost. Many hotels and lodges have come up in Chittoor that provides quality accommodation to the tourists. These hotels and guest houses of Chittoor offer various facilities like room service, restaurant and bar, parking facility, Wi-Fi, and laundry services depending upon the type of room that tourists have opted for.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport is Tirupati airport which is about 57 kms from Chittoor. Chennai airport is about 130 kms away.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Chittoor is located on NH 4, which connects Mumbai, Pune, Bangalore and Chennai and hence, has good road connectivity to these places. Andhra Pradesh State Tourism Corporation (APSRTC) provides regular buses from different states of Andhra Pradesh to Chittoor.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train </strong>- Chittoor has a railway station and it is connected to major cities like Hyderabad, Tirupati and Chennai etc. by rail.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport</strong>- Chittoor has good intra city commuting bus services which are offered by Andhra Pradesh Tourism. There are many cab facilities which can be booked. In order to visit places like Kailasakonda waterfalls, it is better to hire a private cab.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - JAGAN&#39;S SANDRINO, LOCATED AT SANTHAPET - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;EGG FRIED RICE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - LAKSHMI SARASWATHI MILK, LOCATED AT OTK RD, THOTAPALYAM - (FAMOUS FOR BASANDI IS A SWEET &nbsp;MADE FROM MILK AND SUGAR AND GARNISHED WITH ALMONDS, CASHEW, PISTA AND SAFFRON)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - PADMAVATHI TIFFIN CENTRE, LOCATED AT KR PALLI - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;IDLI, DOSA &amp; SAMBAR )</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(422, 14, 31, 732, 'Andhra Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'EAST GODAVARI', 'landscape-320549_6401.jpg', 'landscape-320549_6402.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Nestled beautifully on the banks of the River Godavari, East Godavari is located in the state of Andhra Pradesh and covers a vast portion of the delta area of the Godavari River. The district headquarters are based in Kakinada and it is one of the densely populated districts of the state. The district is bounded on the north by Vishakhapatnam district and the Orissa State, Bay of Bengal on the east, Khamman district on the south and on the west by West Godavari district. East Godavari Travel Guide is incomplete without a mention of its rich cultural and spiritual legacy. Adurru, Pithapuram, Draksharamam, Shri Bhavanarayana Swamy Temple, Bhimesvara Temple and Coringa Sanctuary are the major places to throng in East Godavari. The major area of the district remains under coconut plantation. The key industries that offer employment and source of livelihood to the people are Fisheries, Plywood unit, Paper Mill and Sugar factories. Kakinada, the district HQ is also famous for its industries such as Fertilizer, Sugar, Natural gas and petroleum, Power generation, Edible oil refineries and Bio fuel plants etc. It is part of a Special Economic Zone (SEZ) and the proposed sectors for investment in the city are Chemical, Petroleum and Petrochemical sectors.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">East Godavari offers plenty of options in terms of accommodation. Dotting with numerous hotels, Lodges, and Inns, this city offers accommodation ranging from affordable lodges to expensive hotels. The rooms of the East Godavari hotels are comfortable and spacious laced with all basic amenities. There are few up market hotels like three star hotels and four hotels in Kakinada, which cater to leisure as well as business travellers which offer elegantly furnished accommodation, the deluxe hotels in East Godavari also provide host of facilities to guests including swimming pool, gymnasium, in house restaurants, foreign exchange, car parking, tour desk, and meeting rooms etc.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport is Rajahmundry Airport. The airport is nearly one hour drive from Kakinada. The nearest international airport is Visakhapatnam Airport, around 163 kms away from Kakinada city.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Road</strong> - State buses ply at regular intervals from places like Vijayawada, Hyderabad, Narsapur and Rajahmundry. A well maintained network of motor able roads made road transportation from nearest towns and cities to East Godavari convenient.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>By Train</strong> - Kakinada Junction connects the cities of East Godavari to major Indian cities by several trains. The second nearest railway station is Samalkot Railway Station, located around 12 kms from Kakinada.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(423, 14, 31, 732, 'Andhra Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'GUNTUR', 'ayutthaya-1606479_640.jpg', 'ayutthaya-1606479_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Located in Andhra Pradesh, Guntur is the largest city in the district and is the civil centre of the state. It is situated 64 kms from Bay of Bengal and is easily approachable to the big cities of the state. There are many astounding places such as the Bhattiprolu, Sitanagaram and Amravati that can be viewed in Guntur. Guntur is historically famous for the Buddhism religion and it is said that Buddha himself featured the first Kalachakra at this location. Guntur Travel Guide is incomplete without a mention of its religious destinations, serene spots and rich heritage. Mangalagiri, Kondaveedu, Krishna Barrage, Nagarjuna Sagar Dam and Ethipothala Falls are the famous tourist pearls of the city. Guntur experience diversified culture and has influences from all religions like Hinduism, Buddhism and Islam. It is also famous as the major centre for Textiles, Cotton, tobacco and chilli products that are exported to different parts of the world from Guntur. The city also organizes the largest Asian market for red chillies. This town gives you a unique experience which showcases a beautiful blend of Hinduism, Buddhism and Islam. The city displays plethora of captivating relics of its past including Amravati Caves, Nagarjunakonda and many more. Also renowned as textile hub and transport hub of India, it is a centre of learning as well. Once being the home to numerous great dynasties, today this city is more known for its industrial growth and exports of chilli products to various parts of the globe. An ideal place for history lovers, Guntur was once occupied by several mighty rulers and today promises to take you back once again to the excursion trip of its glorious past.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Guntur offers various options of accommodation all ranging from mid range to budget hotels. Offering a comfortable stay, they also provide good service. Some of the famous hotels in area include Geetha regency Hotel, Sindoori Hotels, Vajram Residency etc.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Flight</strong> - Guntur does not have an airport of its own. Vijayawada serves as the nearest domestic airport situated at a distance of around 96 kms while Hyderabad serves as the site of international airport lying about 250 kms away.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong>- Guntur is afforded with a well maintained network of roads that ensures a very comfortable road journey to the city. There are many buses that plies to the city both state owned as well as private.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - Guntur houses a railway station that is well connected to many major cities of India via good network of regular trains. The network helps connect the city to several metropolitan cities as well including Chennai, Mumbai, Delhi and Kolkata.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport</strong> - A best way for a tourist who is looking for some adventure and unusual trip should go for a bus ride in the Guntur which is quite cheap and convenient mode of transportation. Other than that taxi is best way of commutation for those who came planned with the itinerary of the city. Taxi, although a bit expensive than bus but is much smoother and faster ride.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - VICEROY BIRYANI POINT, LOCATED AT BEHIND ANDHRA BANK, ARUNDELPET - (FAMOUS FOR BIRYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - AMARAVATHI FOOD COURT, LOCATED AT PRATHIBA COMPLEX, NEAR GARDEN PETROL PUMP, CHANDRA MOULI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR KABAB AND SHAWARMA IS A MEAT DISH MADE FROM MEAT OF( LAMB, CHICKEN, BEEF) CHOPPED &nbsp;VEGETABLES, PICKLES WRAPED IN BREAD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - BAJARANG SWEETS, LOCATED AT ARUNDELPET - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;JAANGIRI IS A SWEET MADE FROM BLACK GRAM FLOUR, SAFFRON, GHEE AND SUGAR)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - SREE BALAJI GHEE SWEETS, LOCATED AT NEAR KALAMANDEER,NAIDUPET - (FAMOUS FOR DRY FRUIT HALWA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - CHILLIES DHABA, LOCATED AT AMARAVATHI ROAD, GORANTLA - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN AND MUTTON BIRYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - SRI UDAYA SANKAR, LOCATED AT 4TH LANE, BRODIPET - (FAMOUS FOR NORTH INDIAN FOOD)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '');
