(424, 14, 31, 732, 'Andhra Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'KADAPA', 'shrine-289068_640.jpg', 'shrine-289068_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kadapa known previously as Cuddapah is a municipal city that lies in the area of Rayalseema and is located in the south central region of the southern Indian state of Andhra Pradesh. The city derives its name from the Telugu word &lsquo;Gadapa&rsquo; that translates into a threshold or a gate. The reason for this name is that the city is considered as the threshold or the gateway to the holy hill of Tirumala that lies on the western side of Kadapa. The anglicized spelling of Cuddapah was changed to Kadapa in 2010. Kadapa is at a distance of about 412 kms from Hyderabad, the capital city of Seemandhra. The city is located very close to the Penna River. It is located amidst the two mountains of Nallamala and Palakonda. The city became part of the municipal corporation in the post independence era. Kadapa Travel guide is incomplete without a mention of its rich cultural and spiritual legacy. Kadapa was ruled by different kingdoms over the years and thus the rich cultural influence. The Chola Kings ruled the city from 11th to 14th century and later on it was dominated by the Vijayanagar Kingdom. The traces of these different dynasties can be seen in the area even today. It is believed that one of the seven kandas of the Ramayana, Kishkindakanda is assumed to have happened in Vontimitta, Kadapa district, situated at a distance of just 20 kms from the city.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kadapa is a popular tourist destination both among domestic and international tourists. The city offers various kinds of accommodation options like budget hotels and two star and three star hotels with all the amenities. Tourists can also choose from an array of guest houses like Police Guest House and State Guest House on Yerramukkapalli.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - There is a domestic airport at Kadapa that is about 8 kms from the main city. The airport at Kadapa receives flights only from Hyderabad and Tirupati. Tirupati Airport is about 134 kms from Kadapa, but it is again a domestic airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Kadapa is well connected to the other parts of the country via trains. The railway station at Kadapa lies on the Chennai Mumbai railway line. The Kadapa station receives trains fairly regularly from these two cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - There are many private buses as well as state government run buses that ply regularly to the city of Kadapa. The roads are well maintained making the journey comfortable. There are buses coming to Kadapa from nearby towns like Tirupati, Krishnapuram, Vijayawada, Guntur and Hyderabad.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Kadapa is known to have the best developed infrastructure of the roads. National Highway 18 passes through Kadapa which is extensively developed than many other districts of the state. State Highway 31 connects Kadapa with Tirupathi.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - KADAPA - (FAMOUS FOR RAGI SANGATI IS A MEAL MADE FROM RAGI (MILLET) FLOUR, RICE, WATER AND SALT)&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - MAYURA GARDENIA, LOCATED AT OPPOSITE NEHRU PARK, COOPERATIVE COLONY, R K NAGAR, CO-OPERATIVE COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN BIRYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - RAJADHANI FAMILY RESTAURANT,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT OPPOSITE RTC BUS STAND OUTGATE, SLB ENCLAVE, Y.S.NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR FISH CURRY AND MUTTON BIRYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - SAI MOULA CUTMIRCHI CENTER, LOCATED AT N.G.O COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR MIRCHI BAJJI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - ALANKAR CAFE AND RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT BRAHMIN STREET RAVINDRA NAGAR, TRUNK ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR CHAI(TEA), DOSA, IDLI, NOODLES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - CAFE CUDDAPAH, LOCATED AT KOTIREDDY CIRCLE, ALMASPET - (FAMOUS FOR PASTRY AND MILKSHAKE)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(425, 14, 31, 732, 'Andhra Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'VIJAYAWADA (KRISHNA)', 'pink-1635387_640.jpg', 'pink-1635387_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The accommodation facility in Vijayawada is highly developed because of the well established tourism industry. These hotels provide all the required facilities to the travellers for their comfort at a very reasonable rate. These are well maintained and comprise of a variety of amenities including hospitality, television, internet connectivity, telephone service and much more.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The accommodation facility in Vijayawada is highly developed because of the well established tourism industry. These hotels provide all the required facilities to the travellers for their comfort at a very reasonable rate. These are well maintained and comprise of a variety of amenities including hospitality, television, internet connectivity, telephone service and much more.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - It has its own airport known as Vijayawada airport and is situated at a distance of 20 kms from the heart of the city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train </strong>- It has its own junction named as Vijayawada Railway Station, which connects Vijayawada with all other foremost cities in India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Vijayawada is well connected with all the major cities of the state as well as the neighbouring states via Road network.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Bus</strong> - The APSRTC buses connect the city with all the major cities of the state as well as the neighbouring states.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - DOLPHIN&#39;S KARAHI KITCHEN, LOCATED AT NH5 FRONTAGE ROAD, FREEDER ROAD, BESIDE IDBI BANK, OPPOSITE STELLA COLLEGE, RAMACHANDRA NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR BIRYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - R.R&#39;S JOINTS FAMILY RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT SHOP NO.42-3-1, SINGH NAGAR MAIN ROAD, BUDAMERU CENTER, R