(435, 14, 31, 738, 'Gujarat', 'INDIA', 'ANAND', 'cow-759018_640.jpg', 'cow-759018_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Anand is a small district in the state of Gujarat and is incredibly famous as the Milk Capital of India. The large milk production and distribution is attributed to the idea of the dairy co-operative movement in India, Amul (Anand Milk Union Limited). From its humble start in 1947, the brand administered by Gujarat Co-operative Milk Marketing Federation Ltd. has come a long way and is recognized world over for dairy products. A remarkable fact about the organization is that it is collectively owned by around 3 million milk producers in Gujarat, India. Anand also houses Anand Agricultural University and Dairy Development Board of India. Anand travel guide is incomplete without the mention of its nearby areas. Anand or Bliss, as is its literal meaning is a source of happiness for many families in and around the area. Located between Ahmedabad and Vadodara, Anand is around 100 Kms from the capital city of Gandhinagar. Anand and the nearby villages of Petalad and Borsad are known by the local name Charotar which produce vast quantities of Tobacco and are thus collectively also known as the Golden Leaf. Being very fertile and productive, the area of Charotar is also known as pot full of gold coins. Apart from Amul, Educational Institutions and Dairy board, Anand houses the beautiful Swaminarayan and Ranchhodrai Dakor Temple which are a must visit.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Visitors can enjoy a good stay in Anand because of numerous hotels offering best amenities at affordable prices. There are lodges too that offer quality accommodation facilities within budget. Tourists prefer to stay at budget hotels with all amenities provided. Though there are 5 star hotels and other luxury hotels available in Anand, the number is limited.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Nearest airport to Anand is located in Vadodra at a distance of 42 kms. Vadodara is well connected to Anand and can be reached by road, either through hiring a taxi at the airport or catching a bus from the bus station.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Anand is located on the Golden Quadrilateral National Highway 8, which provides it connectivity to most cities in Gujarat. The city is connected by state owned buses and private buses to the farthest corners of Gujarat and neighbouring states.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Anand is a major junction on the Ahemdabad Vadodara rail link. The railway station is centrally located and provides the city connectivity to other major cities. It has direct trains running to Delhi and Mumbai.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Commuting Within Anand</strong> - The best way to commute within the city is through auto rickshaw or a hired cab. Buses also ply within the city providing good connectivity to important places in the city.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - ANAND - [FAMOUS FOR KATHIYAWAD CUISINIES ARE THE LASSAN ALOO, SEV TAMATAR]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - MOM&#39;S CAFE, AT MAHADEV, VALLABH VIDHYANAGAR - [FAMOUS FOR COLD COFFEE AND MILK SHAKES]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - HAVMOR EATERY, V.V NAGAR ROAD VALLABH VIDHYANAGAR - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;PANNER TIKKA, KAJU CURRY, TANDOORI ROTI, DUM BIRYANI, AND CHANNA PURI]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - HUNGRY RESTAURANT, AT LOCATED AT RAJODPURA - [FAMOUS FOR NON VEGETARIAN DISHES LIKE BUTTER CHICKEN AND FISH CURRY]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - SAHYOG RESTAURANT, AT AMUL DAIRY ROAD, BESIDE HOMEOPATHIC COLLEGE - [FAMOUS FOR PAPAD, JEERA RICE, DAAL FRY AND CHHASS]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - FOOD MASTEE, AT ANSH AVENUE OPPOSITE AKRUTI NAGAR SOCIETY - [FAMOUS FOR SOUTH INDIAN, CHINESE, PAV BHAJI, VADA PAV, BURGERS, FRANKIE]</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(436, 14, 31, 738, 'Gujarat', 'INDIA', 'BHARUCH', 'india-313_1280.jpg', 'india-313_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Bharuch is located on the banks of river Narmada. The city is quite ancient as it exists since the era of Mahabharata. Historians have different names like Bharuch, Bhrigutirth and Bhrigukachchha. This prehistoric city also had importance during the Solanki rule. Bharuch is a shopping centre well known for its salty peanuts. Bharuch people are the followers of different religions and they live in accord. This ancient city is not left with many heritage places but in present times the city has a set up of heavy industries. This is one of the most industrialized cities in Gujarat. There are big chemical plants manufacturing paints, dyes, cotton, textiles, fertilizers and dairy products. Bharuch city is known for fertilizer plants, chemicals and IT services. Bharuch is the oldest city of Gujarat and is located at the mouth of River Narmada. It is a centre of International trade and has a rich archaeological and mythological history too. The place has a lot of mythological relevance. According to Hindu mythology, the Skanda Purana says that Bharuch was the residing place of Goddess Lakshmi before it was visited by Bhrigu Rishi who visited the place which was once a village. The Jain mythology and Buddhist mythology too have mentioned Bharuch in their scriptures. The place is however considered as a tirtha for the Jain community. Since the 1st Century AD, the Bharuch port was considered as a major seaport till the 16th century since the Arab traders used to enter Gujarat via Bharuch for business purposes. The British and Valandas also considered Bharuch as an important centre for business. Bharuch is the only place in the world that celebrates Megharaj Festival (Rain festival) which happens during the month of Shravan.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">a). Ankleshwar<br />\r\nAnkleshwar is a small town in the Bharuch district of Gujarat and is incredibly famous for Shri Ankleshwar Tirth Pilgrimage which includes the four Jain temples. Located at a distance of 10 kms from Bharuch, Ankleshwar is a wonderful city to plan for holidays. There are many amazing historical places and attractions for sightseeing. The flora and fauna of the area is exclusive in the truest sense. Ankleshwar City Guide is incomplete without a mention of its industrial progress. Ankleshwar, also famous as Gujarat&rsquo;s city of oil is known for its industrial township called Gujarat Industrial Development Corporation (GIDC). This city has over a thousand chemical plants, manufacturing products such as insecticide, pharmaceuticals, paints, and chemicals. There are many giant market players in Ankleshwar like Asian Paints, Gharda Chemicals, Godrej, LUPIN, Sun Pharma, Sandoz, United Phosphorous, Glaxo etc.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Quality accommodation is available in Bharuch. Staying in luxury hotels will save money with good amenities offered at economical rates. Tourists can enjoy a good stay in Bharuch because of budget hotels offering best facilities with the best hospitality standards.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Bharuch does not have an airport within city limits however the nearest airports to Bharuch are Vadodara airport at a distance of 85 kms and Surat airport at a distance of about 84kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Bharuch railway station is always a hustling and busy junction. There are over 40 pairs of trains passing through this junction on the Mumbai Delhi line. Bharuch has broad gauge rail line which is about 50 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Bharuch has the facility of buses Interstate and Intra district and these buses travel frequently. Bharuch is connected with various cities of Rajasthan, Gujarat, Delhi, Madhya Pradesh and Maharashtra with the help of these State transport buses and private luxury coaches.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Bharuch has National Highway 8 which connects it to other major cities like Delhi and Mumbai.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Tourists can travel in buses and auto rickshaws in Bharuch which are easily accessible and affordable as well. There are also private bus operators in Bhrauch offering local services to travel within the city as well as around the city. Tourists can also travel locally in Bharuch by hiring taxis which is very convenient to travel.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SHREE KHODIYAAR KATHIYAWADI DHABA, AT BHAGVATI ENCLAVE BUILDING, OPPOSITE GOVERDHAN HOSPITAL, BHOLAV - [FAMOUS FOR KATHIAWADI FOOD]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - REAL PAPARIKA, IN SRI RANG COMPLEX, ZADESHWAR ROAD, NEAR ESSARPETROL PUMPO BHOLAV - [FAMOUS FOR VARITIES OF ICECREAM AND MASALA COLD DRINK]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - KIRAN DABEHLI AND PAVBJHAJI , SHOP NO 6, ABHINAV AVENUE, TAVRA ROAD, NEAR ZADESHWAR CHOWKI ZADESHWAR , GANESH SHRISHTI, VADADLA - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;FAST FOOD ITEMS]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - DASTARKHWAN&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;JHANGHAR, GUJARAT - [FAMOUS FOR NON VEGETARIAN DISHES]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - CHOICE SNACK BAR, AT J.K.COMPLEX, AAALEKH &nbsp;SOSIEIETY, BHOLAV - [FAMOUS FOR GRILLED SANDWICHES, BHEL, VARITIES OF SHAKES AND ICECREAM]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - BAKE QUAKE 1, AT SEVASHRAM ROAD, MOTI DOONBGRI - [FAMOUS FOR VARITIES OF CAKES AND BAKED ITEMS]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - BHARUCH - [FAMOUS FOR SHAAK(COOKED WITH VEGETABLES) MAKAI GHARI (IS A sweet ), KHICHU (IS DOUGH MADE FROM GRAINS), UNDHIYU(MADE FROM MIX VEGETABLES DISHES), KHAMAN(SNACK MADE FROM CHANNA FLOUR), PHAPHADA]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(437, 14, 31, 738, 'Gujarat', 'INDIA', 'BHUJ', 'india-1514744_1280.jpg', 'india-1514744_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Bhuj is the beautiful city which is situated in the Kachchh district of Gujarat. It is the home of the first Swaminarayan Sampraday temples. This temple was built in the year of 1822. People visit this city to view temples, wooden pavilions and palaces. Local people of the city decorate their houses with mud and mirrors. Many historic monuments and structures have made this city most visited destination. Bhartiya Sanskruti Darshan, Swaminarayan Temple, Aina Mahal, Kachchh Museum, Kakkad Bhit Yaksha and many more are the famous sightseeing of the city. This city was built in the year of 1510 by Rao Hamirji. In 1549, it was made the state capital by Rao Khengarji. In earlier times this city was ruled by the British and was an independent part of the Princely States. After independence Bhuj has become a part of India. Batik textiles and intricate silk embroidery are seen in the markets of the city. The City name was derived from the name of the Bhujia Fortress. Now, this Bhujia Fortress is located on a nearby hill which offers a scenic view. This city is located at the heart of Kutch peninsula. It is the best tourist place which has rich heritage and culture. Oldest museum of Gujarat is also situated in this city which is also the most visited tourist place.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Bhuj is the city where perfect accommodation facilities are provided even in the Budget Hotels. Tourists can look for luxury amenities in certain 3 start hotels as well. There are a number of mid range and low budget hotels as well and a few top end hotels of which most of them are situated in and around the New Station Road.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\n<strong>By Air</strong> - Bhuj has its own domestic Airport located in the heart of the city where daily flights operate to Ahmedabad and Mumbai. Kingfisher Airlines and Jet Airways from Bhuj to Mumbai can be availed.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Bhuj has its own Railway Station which is connected to Ahmedabad, Mumbai, Delhi and other major cities of India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Excel Bus Stop in Bhuj is located at a distance of 23 kms from the city from where one can avail government run GSRTC bus services to various destinations in Gujarat.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Bhuj is well connected with nearby cities such as Gandhidham and Mundra. Metered taxis are available for rent from other places inside the city. Even private cabs too could be considered for a budget travel from prominent places to and from Bhuj.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Tuk-tuks are the best way to travel within the city. It&rsquo;s convenient, easy and even cheaper if one knows how to bargain. Charges quoted initially by the drivers might be exorbitant, so be sure to bargain right.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - BHARAT JUICE CENTRE, AT CLOSE TO THE BUS STATION - [FAMOUS FOR MILKSHAKES, FRESH JUICES AND ICECREAM]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - RAAS VATIKA, LOCATED AT VARDHMAN NAGARV - [FAMOUS FOR KAJUKADI, AND MADARASI FOOD]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - FARZANA RESTAURANT,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;NEAR SARPAT GATE, ALAWLA KABRASTAN ROAD, IN FRONT OF JIJAMA DARGAH - [FAMOUS FOR NON VEGETARIAN DISHES]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - THANCO&#39;S NATURAL ICE CREAM,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;AAKASHDEEP COMPLEX, OPPOSITE RELIANCE PETROL PUMP, AIYA NAGAR - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;VARITIES OF ICECREAM]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - NOORANI RETAURANT, AT DANDA BAZAR, KHATRI CHOWK, OLD DHATIAFALIA - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;BUTTER PARATHA, TANDORI CHICKEN, MUTTON DISHES AND KEBAB]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - BHUJ - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;GUJARATI THALI (WITH ROTLAS,MIX VEGETABLES, SEV TOMATO, LENTILS, KADHI) ; SNACKS ARE KHAKARA, THEPALA, FAFDA, KHANDVI, HAHDWOH, GHEWAR, PURAN POLI, BASUNDI ; DABELI (A PATTY SPICY POTATO MIXTURE MADE FROM ONIONSWEET SAUCE, MASALA PEANUTAND POMEGRANTE SEED)]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(438, 14, 31, 738, 'Gujarat', 'INDIA', 'DEVBHOOMI DWARIKA', 'as21.jpg', 'as22.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Dwarka, a city that was known as Dwarawati in Sanskrit literature is one of the seven most ancient cities of India. This city was the abode of Lord Sri Krishna. It is the only place considered both as one of the char dham, as well as one of the sapta puris in our religious texts. The name Dwarka is derived from the word Dvar that means Door in Sanskrit and the significance of this word is the door to Brahma. The city has special significance to the Vaishnavas. The Jagatmandir temple here has the idol of Dwarkadhish, a form of Lord Krishna. Beyt Dwarka is the place where it is believed that Lord Krishna had established his kingdom. This Island, situated in the Gulf of Kutch, is a small island and was the main port in this region before Okha developed it as a port. Dating back to the 3rd century BC can be traced in this island. Beyt Dwarka is also linked with legend where Lord Vishnu killed the demon Shankhasura and so this island is also known as Beyt Shankhodhara. The city of Dwarka is located in the Jamnagar district of Gujarat. The weather in Dwaraka remains beautiful almost throughout the year.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Do not expect any extra ordinary hotels and lodges here. But many small and medium budget lodges are available near the temples. Also, quite a few dharamshalas offer accommodation for Rs. 25-50 per person. A couple of Luxury hotels can also be found.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest domestic airport to Dwarka is the one located at a distance of 127 kms in Jamnagar from where one can pick up a taxi to reach the Dwarka city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - The Dwarka station is located on the Ahmedabad Okha broad gauge railway line where there are trains connecting the city to Rajkot, Ahmedabad and Jamnagar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Located on the state highway from Jamnagar to Dwarka, the city of Dwarka can be easily reached by buses from Jamnagar and Ahmedabad. While the Gujarat State Road Transport buses connect the holy town to all major cities in the state, one can also opt for the luxury tourists buses that ply to the town from almost all the nearby cities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(439, 14, 31, 738, 'Gujarat', 'INDIA', 'DAHOD', 'street-238458_640.jpg', 'street-238458_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Dahod&nbsp;is located on the banks of River Dudhimati in Dahod District in the State of Gujarat, India. The city represents the District Headquarters of Dahod District. It is 200 kms away from Ahmedabad and 150 kms away from Vadodara, respectively. Dahod is alternatively known as Dohad, which means two boundaries. This is because of the fact that the States of Rajasthan and Madhya Pradesh share their borders with the city. Dahod is one of the most economically developed regions of Gujarat state. Despite the fact that Dahod is considered as one of the biggest commodity markets of Gujarat, its economy is largely agrarian due to which the presence of small scale industrial units have attracted a reasonable amount of investors within the region. It is situated on the banks of river Dudhimati. The Mughal Emperor Aurangzeb was born in the fort of Dahod in 1618. The people living in the district are mostly rural. Moreover, a majority of the districts residents are Tribals, mostly Bhils. Jhalod is a large town of historical and commercial importance and serves as administrative headquarters of Jhalod Taluka in Dahod District. Dahod is enriched with its rich history and culture. Its cultural heritage, temples and historic sites attract a huge influx of visitors from all over the world. The town is bedecked with holy mosques and revamped by intricate carvings in the antique temples.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Dahod is the city where perfect accommodation facilities are provided even in the budget hotels. Tourists can look for luxury amenities in certain 3 start hotels as well. It is better to book hotels before beginning the journey to avoid last minute travails.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Vadodara Airport or Civil Aviation Harni, which is at a distance of 150 kms, is the nearest airport to reach Dahod. Tourists can hire local taxis for a cheaper fare to commute to and from all the major parts of the city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Dahod Railway Station is the nearest railway station to reach the city, which is at a distance of 0.7 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Nandava Bus Stand is the nearest bus stand to reach Dahod, which is located at a distance of 16 kms. Private and Government run GSRTC buses can be availed to reach nearby cities in Dahod and major towns in Gujarat.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Dahod is well connected with nearby cities such as Meghnagar, Bhavra and Ranapur. Meter taxis are available for rent from other places near to the city. Even private cabs too could be considered for a budget travel from prominent places to and from Dahod.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - INDORI NASTA HOUSE, LOCATED AT JALVIHAR SOCIETY, NAVJIVAN MILL ROAD NO 2, NEAR SITLAMATA MANDIR - (FAMOUS FOR POHA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - GAB CAFE, LOCATED AT NEAR MUVALIA DAM, OPPOSITE MATRACHAYA SCHOOL - (FAMOUS FOR COFFEE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - 22ND PARALLEL, LOCATED AT GROUND FLOOR, G.L.K. TOWER, STATION ROAD, MOHAMMADI SOCIETY, SWASTIK SOCIETY, SHIDHPUR - (FAMOUS FOR SOUTH INDIAN FOOD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - RATLAMI SEV BHANDAR, LOCATED AT SHANTISADAN SOCIETY, STATION ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR POHE JALEBI, KACHORI AND SAMAOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(440, 14, 31, 738, 'Gujarat', 'INDIA', 'GODHRA', 'crossing-678655_640.jpg', 'crossing-678655_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Godhra is a town and originally the name came from gou which means cow and dhara which has two meanings: one in Sanskrit which means hold or land and the other in Hindi which means flow. So, identically it means The Land of the Cow, a municipality in Panchmahal district in Indian state of Gujarat. It is the administrative headquarters of the Panchmahal district. Godhra is also one of the religious places in the India which has four temples for Vaishnav Sampraday. There are two main seats of are of Lord Gokulnathji, and one each for Lord Gusaiji and Lord Mahaprabhuji. Godhra is the only city in India that has all three seats of the Mahaprabhuji, Gusianji and Gokulnathji. Godhra also has three beautiful Jain temples. Panch Mahal means &quot;Five Palaces&quot; from the district namely Baria, Jambughoda, Lunawada, Santrampur and Champaner. Famous food of the people of Godhra is Maize Bread, Makai No Rotlo. Champaner, a UNESCO World Heritage site is located in this district. Pavagarh hosts a temple of Kalika Mata, whose holy shrine attracts thousands of pilgrims throughout the year.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Not many accommodation facilities available in Godhra. But one can set their base as Halol or Vadodara and experience the magnificence of the Champaner Pavagadh Archaeological Park. There are a lot of accommodation options in Vadodara, because it is one of the major cities of Gujrat.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport to Godhra is Vadodara Airport, Vadodara which is 63 kms away from Godhra city centre.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The nearest railway station to Godhra is Godhra Railway Station which is 4 kms away from Godhra city centre.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - One can conveniently get in Panchmahal by road as it is well connected to National Highway 8 which connects all the major cities of India like, Delhi, Ahmedabad and Gandhinagar etc. So, one can easily get in here via hired taxi or personal car.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong>- The best way to explore the beauty of this place is to travel by foot, though the option of hiring horses is also available. It is a gigantic place but the locales are so splendid that tourists certainly wouldn&#39;t mind treading a few miles for sure.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - THAKKAR KHAMAN HOUSE, LOCATED AT SONIWADA, SHERA - (FAMOUS FOR DHOKLA, JALEBI ,SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - BHAVNAGARI, LOCATED AT PRABHA ROAD, BESIDE PANCHMAHAL TILES FACTORY - (FAMOUS FOR FARSAN IS A SNACK MADE FROM POTATOES AND GRAM FLOUR)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - SHANKAR, LOCATED AT GARDEN ROAD, KACHIAWAD, SONIWADA, SHERA - (FAMOUS FOR PAV BHAJI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - SHREE KRISHNA SWEETS, LOCATED AT OPPOSITE POLICE HEADQUARTER, LALBAGH TEKRI - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORI)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(441, 14, 31, 738, 'Gujarat', 'INDIA', 'JAMNAGAR', 'white-lady-1929722_1280.jpg', 'white-lady-1929722_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Jamnagar is a district in the Indian state of Gujarat. The city was built up substantially by Maharaja Kumar Shri Ranjitsinhji in the 1920s, when the district was known as Nawanagar. Jamnagar is situated at the bank of River Rangmati. Jamnagar is a very beautiful city. It is also known as Saurashtra. The city of Jamnagar, in Gujarat is known to have a few of the uncommon Temples in India. Hence, every year tourists from all over the world flock the city in large numbers to have a look at the finest gifts of history. Among these are visited by the tourists from various parts of India and the world. Among the Temples in Jamnagar, the Bhid Bhanjan Temple, Jamnagar deserves a special mention. Other places are Gaga Wildlife Sanctuary, Lakhota Fort and Museum etc. Maharaja Ranjit Singh was the first popular Indian cricketer ruled here. It is after him, that the name of popular domestic cricket event Ranji Trophy was decided. He also designed European style streets here. There are many old buildings in the city which tell the story of centuries of work in shaping the culture and infrastructure of the city. Today, Jamnagar is very well known for its industrial growth. There is worlds&rsquo; largest oil refinery in the city which belongs to Reliance Petroleum. The central part is the commercial zone and is also popular for its big shopping complexes. The city defines the industrial growth of modern India.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Tourists can choose from a variety of options to stay in Jamnagar. The visitors should go through Jamnagar travel guide to identify the most suitable accommodation for them. Visitors can choose from the options of rented guest houses to budget hotels to the luxury hotels. The accommodation in Jamnagar is available at affordable prices.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The Jamnagar has an airport about 10 kms away from the city centre. Various flights of the domestic airlines fly between Mumbai and Jamnagar daily.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - There are regular trains to places like Ahmedabad, Delhi, Mumbai, Varanasi, Calcutta and Gorakhpur from the Jamnagar Railway Station. The Saurashtra Express and Saurashtra Mail are two popular trains that trip between Mumbai and Jamnagar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Jamnagar is well connected to all major cities via road so one can easily reach here via hired taxi or private car.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Various state transports as well as private AC buses ply to and from cities like Rajkot, Dwarka, Porbandar, Ahmedabad, Bhuj, Surat and other places on a regular basis.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - MADRAS CAFE, AT TEEN BATTI - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;DOSA AND IDLILY]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - JAMNAGAR - [FAMOUS FOR GHUGHARA(KIND OF KACHORI SERVED WITH GARLIC AND CORIANDER CHUTNEY)]</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(442, 14, 31, 738, 'Gujarat', 'INDIA', 'MEHSANA', 'pfalstersteine-602421_640.jpg', 'pfalstersteine-602421_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Mehsana is one of the largest cities in North Gujarat. A number of primary industries including dairy, and oil and natural gas are situated in or around the city. The city is also famous for its local Mehsani buffalo breed, having the first water park in Eurasia, and the largest iron and steel market in India. It is also known for Vadnagar which is a famous town in Mehsana District. If really want to enjoy your day then you could spend your day in Water Park also. Mehsana is also known for high tech educational institution, Ganpat Vidhyanagar. The famous Sun Temple and other Jain temples at Modhera are just about 55 kms from Mehsana. Modhera&#39;s Sun temple is over 900 years old. It is a beautiful town to visit in Gujarat and an apt destination to enjoy the vacations with family. Mahesana Travel Guide is full of references to the religious places and serene spots. Mehsana was found long back during Chawda Dynasty by the renowned King Mehsaji Chavda. City got its name from his first initial and became famous as Mehsana. Mehsaji Chavada established this town during 1358 AD by construction of temple of Goddess Toran and Toran Gate in this town. Later Gaekwads had undertaken the rule of Vadodara and preferred Patan as capital town for that. But later this capital was moved to Mehsana in 1902. Several excavation sites of Indus valley are also found in the region of Mehsana; hence it is believed that habitation was existent during pre historic period.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Mehsana has some of the very ancient and architecturally rich sites visited by hordes of travellers all through the year. This calls for better staying and accommodation in this city. Hence, many hotels are started in Mehsana to cater the increasing demands of these travellers including business travellers and vacationers alike. As these hotels remain booked during peak season of tourism and religious events, it is better to book stay in advance.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Mehsana currently does not possess its commercial airport. It has a small airport for non scheduled flights along with a civil aviation training centre. So to reach the city by air route, tourists have to catch the flights for Ahmedabad Sardar Vallabh Bhai Patel International Airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Mehsana city has great connectivity with the rest of state and entire country through railways. From all the major cities, trains are readily available for this station. The railway junction at Mehsana comes under Western region and Ahmedabad Division of Indian Railways. This station lies on Jaipur Ahmedabad line.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Mehsana is connected with the whole state through its state highways. To cover the distances of these highways, city is blessed with a strong network of roadways buses run by GSRTC. These buses connect Mehsana with other cities of Gujarat that include Gandhinagar, Patan, Ahmedabad, Palanpur, and Unjha. For the convenience of travellers, there are options of Volvo Ac buses, Volvo AC Sleeper coaches, AC Seater coaches, Non AC Sleeper buses, and Non AC Seater buses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Many buses run within the city limits as well as in the entire district to serve the rural areas with better transportation facilities. For those commuters who seek more comfort and prompt services to reach their destination, there are auto rickshaws operating in Mehsana. Car rental services can also be availed by the tourists and business travelers for comfortable travelling in this city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - MEHSANA - [FAMOUS FOR SUKHDI IS A SWEET MADE FROM WHEAT FLOUR AND JAGGERY ; GujaratI SNACKS ARE &nbsp;SEV MAMARA( IS A SNACK IT IS AMIXTURE OF SPICY DRY INGREDIENTS SUCH AS PUFFED RICE, SAVOURY NOODLES AND PEANUTS), LOCHO IS A SNACK MADE FROM GRAM FLOUR), HANDVO IS AVEGETABLE CAKE MADE FROM BOTTLE GUARD ; vegetable (SHAAK INCLUDES BATAKA VATANA SHAAK, CHOLA NU SHAAK, DUDHI NU SHAAK, FANSI NU SHAAK, GUAR NU SHAAK, METHI NU SHAAK) ;&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(443, 14, 31, 738, 'Gujarat', 'INDIA', 'MORBI', 'architecture-1854242_640.jpg', 'architecture-1854242_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Situated at the banks of the River Machhu, Morbi provides a marvellous example of the fusion of traditional and the European style of architecture. The Suspension Bridge through which one approaches the city was built during the British era and is an example of the technological advancement of that era. The city has three gates, and from all these three, the city centre Green Chowk can easily be accessed because the city planning was done by imitating the European style. Right across the bridge is the Darbargadh or the Old Palace which has a beautifully carved front gate and has been currently converted into a Heritage Hotel. The Wellington Secretariat also has the influence of the Rajasthani style in its architecture. Then, there is the Art Deco Palace which reflects the influence of the Art Deco Movement of Europe. The weather of Morbi is extreme and all the seasons quite prominent.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Morbi is not only a tourist spot; it is also an industrial centre. Therefore, it is natural that the town will have number of hotels located in and around the city. As usual, hotels in Morbi fall into different categories. While some fall under budget category, some under three star categories and some are included under five star categories. On the contrary, if looking for heritage hotel, one can book a room at Neemrana Hotel at Darbargarh Palace.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\n<strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport to Morbi is the Rajkot Airport at distance of 66 kms and reachable through State Highway 24.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The closest railway station is Wankaner Junction at a distance of 42 kms. Many trains connecting to different cities of Gujarat and India pass through Wankaner.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Travelling by road to and from Morbi is comparatively easier and hassle free. The city is well connected to other parts of the state through a network of National Highway 8A and State Highways.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - For intra state travel, one can either avail buses belonging to Gujarat Corporation State Road Transport or use private transportation. The fleet consists of luxury, semi luxury, express, ordinary and sleeper buses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong>- For intra city travel, auto rickshaws are best means. Local buses are the best mode of transport for travelling around the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - CHATKAZZ, at Sadhana Complex, Ravapar Road, Opp. IndusInd Bank, Morbi - [FAMOUS FOR BURGER, PIZZA AND SANDWICHES]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - MORBI - [FAMOUS FOR RAGDA IS A FAST FOOD SNACK MADE FROM YELLOW PEAS, POTATOES AND SPICES), PATRA IS A SWEET, SALTY AND SPICY DISH MADE FROM GRAM FLOUR AND AMIXTURE OF SPICES]</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(444, 14, 31, 738, 'Gujarat', 'INDIA', 'NADIAD', 'road-1283158_640.jpg', 'road-1283158_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Nadiad is a place in Kheda district of Gujarat in India. Nadiad is well known for many things. Once upon a time, people like Haridas Biharidas of Nadiad were the flames of public service. The seat of Santaram Maharaj and the Santaram Temple earned fame not only for its religious importance, but for the public service activities also. Nadiad was also the land of laureates and literatures during the later years of l9th century and beginning of the instant. Nadiad is situated at the bank of river Shedhi. Naidad is famous for holy town Dakor. Dakor is famous for Ranchhodji Shri Krishna temple. Nadiad is also famous for its quality education. Famous Dharamsinh Desai Institute of Technology is offering programs in Technology and Management.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Nadiad is wonderful city with different tourists attractions situated in and around the city, and is surrounded by large numbers of small as well as big luxurious hotels, restaurants, resorts as well as the guest houses within the budget. Almost all the hotels have an awesome Panoramic view from their Room that gives a great pleasure for the guests, who wants to watch the nature from above. There are certain hotels which provides nice swimming pool; even one will enjoy the spa at certain hotels. Travellers can choose such hotels which are nearer to the attractions they would like to visit.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\n<strong>By Air </strong>- Nadiad does not have an airport. Nearest airport is Ahmedabad Airport 47 kms away from Nadiad.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Nadiad is on the Western Railway network and is well linked with the rest of the country. Express and local trains provide convenient daily connections to Nadiad from Ahmedabad.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Nadiad has a good road network as National Highway 8 and State Highway 228 passes via Nadiad town. The State Transport Corporation connects it to all the major cities and towns of Gujarat and other states of the country.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - WOODLANDS RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT NH 8, SHANTI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR SOUTH INDIAN FOOD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - NEW INDIA RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT DABHAN BHAGOLE, JUNARAOPURA, NEAR NAGAR PALIKA - (FAMOUS FOR MANGO SHAKE)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - CHEESE N CHIPS, LOCATED AT 110, GRAVITY COMPLEX, COLLEGE ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - BIHARI, LOCATED AT MANEK CHOWK - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - AAZAD PANIPURI CENTER, LOCATED AT RABARI VAAD, BAPU NI FACTORY, JUNARAOPURA - (FAMOUS FOR PANI PURI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n6 - PUROHIT PANCHAVATI, LOCATED AT NH 8, NEAR, NADIAD - (FAMOUS FOR DAL BATI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n7 - SAI, LOCATED AT COLLEGE ROAD, VANIYAWAD, AKSHAR TWP - (FAMOUS FOR CHEESE VADA PAV)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>8 - NEW JYOTI REFRESHMENT, LOCATED AT SHRI SANTRAM MANDIR MARG, SHANTI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR DAL PURI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>9 - KING RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT JUNARAOPURA - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN FRIED RICE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>10 - BOMBAY RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT JUNARAOPURA - (FAMOUS FOR KABAB AND SAMOSA)&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>11 - DHANLAAL NI DABELI, LOCATED AT OPPOSITE NOKIA CARE,NEAR VANIYA VAAD, SH 61 - {FAMOUS FOR DABELI IS A SNACK MADE FROM POTATOES, MASALA, PAV (BURGER BUN) GARNISHED WITH POMEGRANATE AND ROASTED PEANUTS AND SERVED WITH CHUTNEY ( MADE FROM TAMARIND, DATE, GARLIC, RED CHILIES)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>12 - SHRINAATH PAV BHAJI, LOCATED AT NANA KUMBHNATH ROAD, SHANTI NAGAR - {FAMOUS FOR PAV BHAJI &nbsp;AND PULAV (MADE FROM RICE)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>13 - NAVINCHANDRA SOMABHAI BHAVSAR, LOCATED AT SANTH BAZZAR, JUNARAOPURA - (FAMOUS FOR MIX CHEVADA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>14 - SHREE DAS BARFIWALA, LOCATED AT SANTRAM TOWER, DUMRAL BAZAR, KAKARKHAD BARI, DUMRAL BAZAR, JUNARAOPURA - (FAMOUS FOR KAJU KATLI, BARFI AND NAMKEEN LIKE FARALI CHEVDA AND SEV)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(445, 14, 31, 738, 'Gujarat', 'INDIA', 'NARMADA (RAJPIPLA)', 'narmada-238995_640.jpg', 'narmada-238995_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Narmada district is a district in the state of Gujarat in India. The district headquarters are located at Rajpipla. The princely state of Rajpipla was situated largely between two important rivers of western India, the Narmada and the Tapti, with the Satpura range in the south. This district is famous for Narmada River and temples at the bank of the river. Ths Marble rock along the river is quite mesmerising. It is also famous for some Anthropological sites. There are dams and canals are constructed on this river. The name of the district is inspired on the name of &quot;Narmada River&quot;. Ratanmahal Sloth Bear Sanctuary, Shoolpaneshwar Wild Life Sanctuary etc are famous wild life sanctuaries in the city. This town is surrounded by thick forests and hills on all sides; several small streams, rivulets, view points and watering holes are also located here. The town is located downstream from the Narmada Dam. This town reflects Gujarati tradition to its core, with dhotis and saris being the main attire of locals. Navratri is celebrated on a large scale and people take part in the Garba and Dandia enthusiastically. The Government is heavily promoting tourism in Narmada due to its scenic location and wild life and plant species. The area also serves as a spot for leisure and recreational activities such as mountaineering, surfing and boating.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Narmada provides its visitors a whole range of options to choose from. From luxury star hotels to economic accommodation with facilities apt for a comfort stay to guest houses with just basic facilities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport to Rajpipla is Vadodara Airport, Vadodara which is 58 kms away from Rajpipla city centre.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train </strong>- The nearest railway station to Rajpipla is Itola Railway Station which is 40 kms away from Rajpipla city centre.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Bharuch, Rajpipla, Chanod, and Dabhoi are accessible by buses. The Sardar Sarovar dam site can be reached by private vehicle.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SHREE RAM RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT SH 160, RAJENDRA NAGAR SOCIETY - (FAMOUS FOR GUJARATI THALI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - KOHINOOR FARSAN MART, LOCATED AT STATION ROAD,NEAR WHITE TOWER, RAJPUT FADIA - (FAMOUS FOR BATATA VADA AND POHA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - SAI LIVE DHOKDA, LOCATED AT MV RD, RAJENDRA NAGAR SOCIETY - {FAMOUS FOR DHOKLA IS A SNACK MADE FROM BESAN (CHICKPEA FLOUR) AND RICE FLOUR}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - KAPIRAJ, LOCATED AT BHADAAM - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;BANANA WAFERS)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(446, 14, 31, 738, 'Gujarat', 'INDIA', 'NAVSARI', 'mahatma-178653_640.jpg', 'mahatma-178653_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Navsari district is located in the south eastern part of Gujarat state in the coastal low land along Purna River. The district has 5 talukas of which Gandevi and Chikhli are major talukas. The district abounds in sugarcane fields, chikoo plantations, and mango trees. Navsari is known for its floriculture activities and sugar business. The focus sectors of the district are agro and food processing industries, textiles, drugs and pharmaceuticals, mineral related industries and marine based industries. Famous historical places both Dandi and Vansda National Park are located in Navsari. The pioneer of the Indian steel industry and the founder of the House of Tatas, Mr. Jamshedji Tata was born in Navsari. The house where he was born is well preserved and recommended for a visit. The Atash Behram, situated close to the Tarota Bazar in Navsari and one of the seven Atash Behrams in the world, is visited by numerous Parsi Zoroastrians. The coastline close to the city holds an important place in the modern history of India. The Dandi March, the first major revolt against the British rule, took place in the village of Dandi which is situated in the coastline.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are many hotels which provide accommodation in the city of Navsari which include Hotel Sauras, Hotel Ashoka, Hotel Anmol, Hotel Royal Regency etc. that provide accommodation here along with other budget hotels as well.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Navsari does not have an airport. Nearest airport is Surat Airport 26 kms away from Navsari.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Tourists can easily get regular trains to Navsari from other major cities of the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - There are regular buses from other major cities of the country to Navsari.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - It is also well connected by roads via National Highway 8 which runs through the place.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - There are auto rickshaw facilities in Navsari which have a fixed rate for every particular destination that tourists want to visit. There are also buses run by the state transport department.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - KRISHNA STALL - [FAMOUS FOR PAV BHAJI]<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(447, 14, 31, 738, 'Gujarat', 'INDIA', 'PALANPUR', 'steeple-949312_640.jpg', 'steeple-949312_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">A wonderful city to visit in the affluent state of Gujarat, Palanpur is the largest city in Banaskantha district and is the administrative headquarters of the district. The town is a very important place for pilgrims due to the existence of many temples in the region. Thus, the town of Palanpur attracts many tourists who flock to this town from all parts of the country to experience the holy and religious spirit and local festivities all through the peak season. As per the myth; it was first established by a Prahladan, member of the Paramara tribe of Rajputs, who got the area as a gift from his elder brother and ruled the regime of what is at present Mount Abu. Palanpur travel guide is full of references to the mesmerizing sceneries and religious spots. In the history of Jainism Palanpur was known as Prahladanpur. The town later became the part of the royal state in British India. It was once fortified with seven gates offering the only means of driveway. Delhi Gate, Meera Gate, Shimla Gate, Vir Bai Gate and Gathaman Gate are the famous gates.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">a). Deesa<br />\r\nDeesa, a city and taluka of district Banaskantha in Gujarat State, is one of the two important cities of the district. The city holds an important place in the tourist map of the state. This city is also known for its market of agricultural products. Numerous temples of Deesa and the beautiful Banas River make it one of the most preferred tourist destinations of the recent time. Deesa is a town located in the heart of Banaskantha District of Gujarat. The town is situated on the banks of River Banas. &nbsp;The town was ealier recognised by the name of Camp Deesa, when it was under the rule of Deewan Saheb. In today&rsquo;s time, these localities are recognised by the name of New Deesa. The town of Deesa is popular for potato plantations. The place is surrounded by several tourist destinations situated at distances of not more than 140 kms. Winters are pleasant and cool and offer a mild weather with cool winds, making this time ideal for outdoor and sightseeing activities. The best time to visit this town comes in between the months of October and March.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">To cater to the requirements of large number of tourists visiting Palanpur ever year, many luxury and budget hotels have come up to cater to the requirements of all classes of people visiting the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport to Palanpur is Ahmedabad&#39;s Sardar Vallabhai Patel International Airport situated at a distance of 135 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - Palanpur railway station is part of the Western Railways of the Indian Railways. This junction is directly linked on broad gauge to various cities like Bangalore, Chennai, Delhi, etc. The town is well connected by rail to all major cities of Gujarat too.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - State Highway 712 and SH 132 pass by Palanpur, thus connecting it with a few important cities of Gujarat. SH 41 connect the city to Ahmedabad. National highway 14 also passes through Palanpur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Bus</strong> - All the governments and private buses ply from the bus depot to various cities within Gujarat and also to other nearby states. The buses charge reasonable rates and are quite comfortable to travel in. Luxury buses with AC facilities are also available. Sometimes the buses are also booked for local touring purpose by the tourism department of Gujarat or the local travel agencies of Palanpur.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - PALANPUR - [FAMOUS FOR MAGAS IS SWEET DISH MADE FROM COMBINATION OF BESAN, SUGAR AND GHEE) ; KATHOL(PUSES) WITH Chutney ; KANGRA TEA JHOL(DRINK MADE OF RICE WATER)]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '');
