(448, 14, 31, 738, 'Gujarat', 'INDIA', 'PATAN', 'milestone-346842_1280.jpg', 'milestone-346842_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Patan is the former capital of Gujarat. The ancient, fortified town was built by the then king Vanraj Chavda in 745 AD. Attacked by Mohamud Ghazni in AD 1024, the city sprung from its ruins only to become the Suba headquarters of Sultanate Delhi, before it was known as the capital city of the Gujarat Sultanate. Famous for its exquisitely woven Patola saris, Patan is a hub of the finest made textiles in the world. During the Solanki period, the glory of Patan reached its peak. It was known as the Golden age of Gujarat. The rulers of Patan were great patrons of art and architecture. A number of civic as well as religious buildings were constructed in the city, including many Hindu, Muslim and Jain religious places. However, the Jain temples outnumber the others. These monuments are a major attraction from travel and tourism point of view. The foreign tourists throng the city, to view the amazing monuments adorned with intricate carvings and sculptures. The city was also known as Anhilwad Patan as it was named after Anahil, the shepherd friend of King Vanraj. Presently, Patan is also famous for the Patola saris that are woven in Salvivad by the Mashru weavers.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Patan provides its visitors a whole range of options to choose from. From luxury star hotels to economic accommodation with facilities apt for a comfort stay to guest houses with just basic facilities. Please discuss the needs and requirements and negotiate the charges before finally reserving accommodation.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Sardar Vallabhai Patel Airport at Ahmedabad is the nearest Airport to Patan. Flights are available to both domestic and International destinations from here.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - There is no railway station in Patan. The nearest Railway Station to Patan is at Mehsana which would be more than an hour&#39;s journey from the city. From Mehsana trains are available to all the major cities in India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - From Gandhinagar, intercity buses are available to Mehsana from where buses are available to other destinations in India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Patan being a small town, many historical monuments and other exhibits can be visited by walking. Travellers who want to roam around this ancient town can enjoy doing so by visiting various places of interest on foot. Many lanes and by-lanes of this town are not appropriate for vehicles. There are auto rickshaws available on rent. Those who cannot walk for long or for elderly people and kids, auto rickshaws can be hired for the entire day to roam around and enjoy various tourist spot in and around Patan.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - PATAN - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;PIE IS TYPE A PASTRY]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - JAY BHAVANI, at Madhav Twins, Opp Chintamani Flats, College Road Raj Mahal Roa - [FAMOUS FOR VARITIES OF PAV BHAJI]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(449, 14, 31, 738, 'Gujarat', 'INDIA', 'PORBANDAR', 'cruise-ship-1218305_640.jpg', 'cruise-ship-1218305_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Porbandar is one of the famous coastal cities of Gujarat. This beautiful tourist spot is well known as the birthplace of Mahatma Gandhi and Sudama, the friend of Lord Krishna. This beautiful tourist destination is the managerial centre of Porbandar District. Travel guide on Porbandar provides information about the city which offers information about its climate and weather. It is another famous and most beautiful city which is well planned and has numerous stone buildings with ashlar masonary and carved with rich artistic designs. The frontage of the houses are located on the either side of the streets integrated with series of windows, engraved gateways and many more that makes it an ideal tourist destination. In the city, there are numerous attractive interesting places which have their own religious significance that magnetizes large number of travellers from all over the country. Porbandar Travel guide is one of the most famous tourist destinations which magnetize religiously inclined people and all those people who like to know about cultural beauty of the country. Porbandar is a beautiful beach town with some temples and dams, and is now also a popular trading hub. The coastal city with a significant event in its history is a tourist destination which modestly offers a number of attractions. Apart from the haveli where Gandhiji was born which has now been converted into a temple, there are a few more temples, dams, reservoirs, serene beaches and wildlife spots as well to add an experience in Porbandar.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are many famous hotels in the city which offers great accommodation and other lodging services to the guest. Here one can choose from low budget hotels to high budget resorts which is purely depends upon the visitors.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Porbandar has a new terminal building built by the Airport Authority of India and there are daily flights to Mumbai from the Porbandar airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Porbandar has a railway station and the city is well connected by rail to all the major cities of the state and country. There are trains to Okha, Rajkot, Mumbai and Bhanwad daily.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Porbandar city is connected to Rajkot and Ahmedabad through the National Highway 8B and is connected to the cities of Dwarka and Jamnagar in the north and Bhavnagar and Verval in South through the NH 8 Extension.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Tourists can easily find different kinds of buses travelling to and from Porbandar. Some of the major ones include Non AC buses, AC Seater cum Sleeper buses, non AC Seater cum Sleeper buses and non AC or AC Sleeper buses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - The responsibility of handling the city&rsquo;s local transportation is managed by city buses which are run by a private company named Kargil Parivahn. Auto Rickshaw is another common means of transport which connect to different corners of the city. Tourists can also find private taxis and city buses operating from Sudama Chowk which is one of the chief points of the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - PORBANDAR - [FAMOUS FOR SNACKS like &nbsp;KHANDIVI( IS A SNACK MADE FROM GRAM FLOUR AND YOGURT), KHAKHARA IS A SNACK &nbsp;MADE FROM MAT BEAN WHEAT FLOUR AND OIL) ; KHAJLI IS SNACK MADE FROM PLAIN FLOUR, GHEE, POWDER OF (TUREMRIC, BLACK PEPPER,CHILLI) ; SWEETS ARE GHEVAR(IS A SWEET CAKE MADE FROM FLOUR, MILK, BUTTER SUGAR, ALMONDS, PISTACHIO, SAFFRON AND CARDAMOM), BASUNDI(IS A SWEET DESERT MADE FROM MOLK SUGAR,CARDAMOM AND SAFFRON)]</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(450, 14, 31, 738, 'Gujarat', 'INDIA', 'SABARKANTHA (HIMATNAGAR)', 'dia-1035835_640.jpg', 'dia-1035835_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Himmatnagar is a town in the district of Sabarkantha in the state of Gujarat and was named after its king Himmat Singh. The town has a long ancient heritage that is represented in the form of its unique architecture of Maharaja Himmat Singh Fort, which is located along the banks of the river Hathmati and Dowlat Vilas Palace. Himmatnagar is religiously important for devotees who travel here to visit temples and pilgrimage spots. The town is also known for being the administrative headquarters of the northern region of Gujarat and the economic development of the town is due to the several ceramic industries and dairies that have established here with time. One such dairy is the Sabar Dairy, which is the branch of Amul Dairy. Himmatnagar has several attractions scattered around the region like Vatkapur Teerth, which is a temple visited by pilgrims from different parts of India. This temple is on the border of Vaktapur Village, on the highway. There are ancient idols of gods like Nakoda Bhairavji, Bhagvan Chintamani Parshwanath and Shri Manibhadravir in the temple. Shri Mehsana Teerth is another ancient temple here that was built in the 15th century and is a place of pilgrimage, which is visited by devotees from different regions. Other temples present here include Shamlaji temple and the Akshardham temple in Gandhinagar. The Calico Museum is also a major attraction. Himmatnagar has an extreme climate with hot and humid summers and chilly winters. Winters are considered the best time to visit this place.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Sabarkantha is a major tourist place and an industrial hub as well so many people visit this city all through the year. There are so many hotels, resorts and guest houses available in this city which provides a place to stay. Tourists who visit this place can avail the facility of many packages which are made available by the hotels. Economical hotels are also there as per the needs of the customers.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Road connectivity is good as Himatnagar is connected to all major cities within easy reach by state run buses or the private mode of transport as autos and rickshaws. The roads are well maintained and are also connected to NH 8 highway.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail</strong> - One can easily board regular trains shunting on and off to Himatnagar from all other major cities of the country. The main Railway junction is the Himatnagar Junction.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Air</strong> - Himatnagar does not have an airport on its name but the nearest Ahmadabad airport is 73 kms away as well the Vadodara airport being 144 kms away. From there on one can take buses to ply to interiors of Himatnagar town.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - JAY BHAVANI, LOCATED AT SHOP 4-5, K B ARCADE, SAHAKARI GYM CROSS ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR VADA PAV)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - SAURASHTRA FAST FOOD, LOCATED AT SH 9, GANOTRI SOCIETY - (FAMOUS FOR PAV BHAJI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - ORANGE CITY FOODS, LOCATED AT TULSI LANDMARK SAHKARI JIN CHAR RASTA - (FAMOUS FOR CAKE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - TALOD GOTA HOUSE, LOCATED AT STATE HIGHWAY 9 OPP.GSRTC BUS STATION, GANOTRI SOCIETY - (FAMOUS FOR BATAKAWADA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - SHREE CHARBHUJA, LOCATED AT GIDC, MOTIPURA - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;PAU BHAJI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - JALARAM, LOCATED AT ASHRAF NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR SEV KHAMNI)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(451, 14, 31, 738, 'Gujarat', 'INDIA', 'TAPI', 'industry-1968193_1280.jpg', 'industry-1968193_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Tapi district is one of the district of Gujarat states in western India. Vyara town is the districts headquarter. Tapi is surrounded Maharastra State from east, from south Navsari and Dang district from west Surat district and Narmada district from from north.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Tapi offers a wide range of accommodation from tourist huts to budget hotels and from 5 star holes and home stays to government guest houses.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Tapi district has excellent connectivity by road to rest of the state and country. National highway 6 passes from the Tapi District.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - Tapi district is well connected by rail network from rest of the state and country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The Nearest airport to Tapi district is Surat Airport.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - TAPI - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;UNDHIYU(PREPARE WITH DIFFERENT TYPES OF VEGETABLES) ; BASUNDI(IS A DESERT MADE FROM MILK, SUGAR, SAFFRON, CARDAMOM) BHAKRI(ROTI) MADE FROM FLOUR ; CHHUNDO(IS A KIND OF PICKLE MADE FROM RAW MANGOES), DABELI(IS ASNACK MADE FROM POTATOES, SPICES AND PAV), DHEBRA(IS ADISH MADE FR0M BAJARA FLOUR), GALYA PULLA(IS A DISH MADE FROM JAGGERY AND WHEAT FLOUR)]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(452, 14, 31, 738, 'Gujarat', 'INDIA', 'THE DANGS', 'waterfall-1888180_640.jpg', 'waterfall-1888180_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\nThe Dangs is a district in the state of Gujarat in India. The administrative headquarters of the district are located in Ahwa. Located high in the Saputara hills, adjoining the borders of Maharashtra State, Dangs is the home of adivasis who have lived in the forest and highlands of the Dangs region from time immemorial. Shri Hanumanji is believed to have been born at Anjani Kund in Southern Gujarat&#39;s Dang district. This city is famous for its fair which is known as dang darbar fair. It is also famous for the Saputara Hill Station which is quite pleasent. You will feel real calm and pleasure here. Dang exists in the Saputara range on the eastern side near the hills of Thane district and forests. The forests of Dharampur of Valsad district lies to its east. The Vansda Dang forests are present in the east of Bilimora, where as to the west is the straight coastline and forest strip. Dang is also known as The Dangs which literally means a hilly terrain. There is also another representation of the word Dangs, which means a place of Bamboo. In ancient Indian scriptures, Dang was known as Dand Aranyaka, meaning Bamboo Forest. Dang was even known as Dakaranya or Dandak during the period of Ramayana. Dang is a vital city of Gujarat from various points of view. It is a hilly forestland and the Adivasi life adds one more dimension to Gujarat&#39;s existing diverse lifestyles. Dang contains several protected forests that the Dangis are allowed to use for cultivation and residence.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Dang is home to budget hotels and guesthouses where tourist boarding and lodging facilities are developed and provided by the Government at nominal rates. It is advisable to book for hotels to avoid last minute rushes, especially during peak festive seasons.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Surat Airport is the nearest airport to reach Dang. The distance covered is 172 kms. Surat is connected to major cities of Gujarat and neighbouring state.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Billimora Railway Station, which is located at a distance of 25 kms from Dang, is the nearest railway station to reach the city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Central Bus Stand of Ahwa is the nearest bus stand to reach Dang. Regular bus services from GSRTC are available for travellers&rsquo; convenience from nearby places.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water</strong> - Hazira Port is at a distance of almost 200 kms from Dang, which is a fully furnished seaport that is connected well with other cities such as Diu, Bhavnagar and Mumbai.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Dang is connected with State Highway 9 which passes through Waghai. Another State Highway 14 connecting Dangs passes connects Waghai and Ahwa.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SWAD RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT SAVSHANTI LAKE RESORT, NAGESHWAR MAHADEV POINT ROAD, SAPUTARA - {FAMOUS FOR MASALA(SPICE) KHICHIDI}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - JOLLY FAST FOOD, LOCATED AT NEAR SAPUTARA LAKE, SAPUTARA - (FAMOUS FOR FRIED RICE AND SANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(453, 14, 31, 738, 'Gujarat', 'INDIA', 'VAPI', 'road-243234_640.jpg', 'road-243234_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">A well developed commercial city of Valsad district, Vapi is located in the affluent state of Gujarat. It is one of the largest cities in the district and the state and is located on the bank of the Damanganga River. Vapi is bounded by outstanding locations for housing and amusement such as Daman and Diu,Dadra and Nagar Haveli, Bhilad, Sarigam, Udavada, Umbergaon, Pardi, Silvassa and Sanjan. Vapi City Guide is incomplete without a mention of its industrial prowess. It is a very significant industrial town and the largest industrial area in Asia in respect of small-scale industries, chemical industry plants. An initiative taken by the Common Effluent Treatment Plant which has been set up in the town in order to reduce pollution is worth appreciating. It is among Asia&rsquo;s biggest plant and is responsible for treating the effluents of industries before they are sent further in the Daman Ganga River. Vapi is the gateway to Daman, where a lot of people go to party and enjoy the beaches.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">a). Valsad<br />\r\nValsad is a coastal district, and it derived its name from vad-saal&#39;, that means hampered by banyan trees. This area was full of banyan trees. Valsad is the first place where the Parsis entered before they found the Sanjan Port. Valsad is surrounded by the Arabian Sea, Navsari and Dang districts and the state of Maharastra. Valsad, formerly known as Bulsar, is a city and a municipality in the Valsad district of the Indian state of Gujarat. The city has a collectorate, a district court, and a police headquarters with a historic prison. Valsad is a small, sleepy town that is characterized by its dynamic people and its mango and chickoo orchards. Queen lead singer Freddie Mercury&#39;s family name is derived from the former name of the city. The best time to visit Valsad is in June July, post monsoon, when the roads in and around town are at their best.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Vapi has abundant facilities for food and lodging for tourists. Several restaurants and hotels are seen in the city. Some are luxury ones while others are the budget hotels. All hotels provide multi cuisine food to customers. Other than the hotels, resorts are also available in Vapi. Perhaps, the ideal time to visit the city is between November and January.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The Vadodara airport is the nearest one to Valsad.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - Valsad is well connected by rail to the major cities of Gujarat as well as India. The Valsad station is on the Mumbai Vadodara mainline.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Bus</strong> - Various state transport buses ply to Valsad from the major cities of Gujarat. Several private luxury buses also travel to Valsad from different cities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - VAPI - [FAMOUS FOR UNDHIU(PREPARE WITH DIFFERENT TYPES OF VEGETABLES), THEPLA(IS A SPICY WHEAT PANCAKE) ; KADHI(IS A YOGHURT CURRY PREPARE WITH VEGETABLES MIX WITH VARIOUS SPICES) ; SNACKS ARE KHAMAN DHOKALA(IS MADE OF CURD AND GRAMFLOUR) GATHIYA(PREPARED WITH SPLIT PEA) ; SWEETS LIKE SUTARFENI(IS A SWEET DISH MADE FROM RICE OR WHEATDOUGH, NUTS AND MELTED WITH SUGAR), HALVASAN( IS A SWEET MADE FROM WHEAT, MILK, GHEE, ALDMONS ANND CARDAMOM POWDER)]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - PARMATMA FOOD AND ICECREAM PARLOUR,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Shop No.23, Daman Rd, Shopper Gate,Near Subham 3, Chala - [FAMOUS FOR VARITIES OF ICECREAM]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(454, 14, 31, 742, 'Karnataka', 'INDIA', 'BAGALKOT', 'krishna-river-200386_640.jpg', 'krishna-river-200386_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Bagalkot is a town and headquarters in Bagalkot district of Karnataka. Lying on the bank of the river Ghataprabha, the District of Bagalkot is the second largest district in the State of Karnataka. The place is situated entirely on the North Karnataka Plateau, which is part of the larger Deccan Plateau. Located in north central Karnataka, Bagalkot is surrounded by Belgaum district to the west, Bijapur district and Gulbarga district to the north and north east, Raichur district to the east and Koppal district, Gadag district and Dharwad district to the southeast, south and southwest respectively. The place got its name as one of the kings of Bijapur had gifted the town to his daughter as bangle or ornament money. Accordingly the place acquired the name of Bagdikot, which was further corrupted to Bagilakote or Bagalkot. Bagalkot was earlier a part of Bijapur district, which was later craved out as a separate district in 1997. This area is home to some of the finest examples of temple architecture in the world. Bagalkot District with its fertile verdant terrains drained by perennial rivers facilitates extensive cultivation has transformed into a major tourist attraction. Being a sightseer&#39;s paradise with its panoramic beauty, today the city of Bagalkot is divided into two parts the new Bagalkot or Navangar and the old Bagalkot town. The construction of new town became necessary following submergence of parts of old town due to construction of Almatti dam. Navangar is a planned town with grid pattern lay out with wide roads, parks and other amenities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Bagalkot offers accommodation to tourists in plenty. Tourists can choose from tourist rest houses, private hotels, lodges and PWD rest houses at reasonable prices. Tourists must make arrangement for accommodation in Badami, which is the nearest town to Aihole and can be reached by road within 40 minutes.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest major airports to Bagalkot are the Belgaum Airport which is 121 kms and the Dabolim Airport in Goa about 218 kms from the centre of Bagalkot, Karnataka.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Railway Bagalkot is connected by a broad gauge railway line to Bijapur on the South Western Railway towards the north and to Gadag junction on the South Western Railway towards the south.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - There are regular buses from other major cities of the country to Bagalkot.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Bagalkot is well connected by road and railway routes. The National Highway NH 218 from Hubli to Humnabad passes through Bagalkot. The state highway passing through Bagalkot connects NH 13 at about 40 kms from Bagalkot.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - BAGALKOT - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;JOLADA ROTTI( IS AN INDIAN BREAD MADE OF JOWAR), BHAKRI(IS A BREAD MADE OF JOWAR FLOUR),KARADANTU(IS A SWEET DISH MADE FROM EDIBLE GUM, DRY FRUITS, JAGGERY, NUT SEEDS) ; FAMOUS FOR KARADANTU(IS A SWEET DISH MADE FROM EDIBLE GUM, DRY FRUITS, JAGGERY, NUT SEEDS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - Himalaya Cold &nbsp;Drinks, IN BAGALKOT - (FAMOUS FOR FRUIT SALAD]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(455, 14, 31, 742, 'Karnataka', 'INDIA', 'BELGAUM', 'suvarna-vidhana-soudha-292736_640.jpg', 'suvarna-vidhana-soudha-292736_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Belgaum was earlier known as Venugrama which means Bamboo Village. This place is one of a few ancient cities, which has preserved its natural beauty as well as its historical places. This beautiful destination is located near the foothills of the Sahyadri mountain range, which are also known as Western Ghats, at an altitude of around 779 mts, 100 kms from the Arabian Sea. Kittur is a place of historical importance in Belgaum district. Queen Chennamma of Kittur is known for her resistance to British rule. Apart from her, Sangolli Rayanna is another person in the history of Belgaum, who is known for his resistance to the British rule. This city has the cultural flavour of Maharashtra, Karnataka and Goa. It is a blend of these three cultures which has created the rich heritage that is purely exclusive in its expression. The district comprises 1278 villages and has an area of 13415 sq kms. Belgaum is the now a commercial hub standing second to Bangalore in terms of overall exports in the state, known as the Bread Basket/Rice Bowl of north Karnataka. It is interesting to know that the city has been selected as one among the 20 cities called as smart cities under PM Modi&rsquo;s Smart Cities Mission.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The city provides quite amazing accommodation facilities to its visitors. There are numbers of renowned hotels and resorts which are infused with advanced technology features that give all kinds of convenience to its guests and many others are some budget friendly hotels.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The airport serving the city of Belgaum is at Sambra, located 10 kms from the city on the State Highway 20.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Belgaum is located on the main Indian Railways network which is now become a part of south western division. This beautiful destination is well linked by rail to other major destinations. Belgaum railway station is considered as the oldest railway station in this region.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - National Highway 4 and 4A are the two national highways that connect the city to places in other states like Karnataka, Goa, Tamil Nadu and Maharashtra.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - The North Western Karnataka Road Transport Corporation (NWKRTC) runs buses that run within the city. There is wide range of well known private buses for visiting Karnataka and nearby states.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1- BELGAUM - [FAMOUS FOR HULI OR DOSA(RICE DOUGH) AND SAMBHAR DAL(MADE OF YELLOW LENTILS, MIX VEGETABLES, SPICES AND COCONUT PASTE) ; PURI UNDE OR MURMURA(IS CALLED LADDOO, MADE OF PUFFED RICE) ; RICE RAVA UPMA(BREAKFAST DISH MADE OF BROKEN RICE AND SOME MILD SPICES) ; RICE APPAM(IS SWEET DISH MADE OF RICE, JAGGERY AND COCONUT) ; JOWAR BHAKRI( IS MADE OF FLAT BREADS) ; BISI BELE BAATH(IS MADE OF RICE, LENTILS AND VEGETABLES) ; RAVA KESARI(SWEET DISH MADE OF SEMOLINA), CHIROTI(MADE FROM &nbsp;MAIDA AND DREEP FRIED IN GHEE) ; MANGO CHUTNEY MADE OF RIPE MANGOES AND SPICES) ; VOGANI MIRCHI(IS A SNACK PREPARED FROM PUFFED RICE) ; RASAM BONDA(SNACK MADE FROM URAD DAL,CHOPPED COCONUT,PEPPER)]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - Tatte Idli, at C D DESHMUKH ROAD TILAKWADI - (FAMOUS FOR Benne Dosa)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - PARATHA CORNER, LOCATED AT CONGRESS ROAD TILAKWADI - (FAMOUS FOR PARATHAS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - GAWDES, LOCATED AT KELKAR BAGH - (FAMOUS FOR SABU VADA PAV)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - NUPUR, MAHATMA PHULE ROAD CROSS SHAHPUR - (FAMOUS FOR MUTTON CHOPS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - BALUS, OPPOSITE RPD COLLEGE ROAD TILAKWADI - (FAMOUS FOR PAV BHAJI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - SUKESH TEA STALL, NEXT TO SARASWEAT BANK GALI - (FAMOUS FOR VARITIES OF TEA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>8 - ZAKIA, LOCATED AT CHURCH STREET CAMP - (FAMOUS FOR SAHI TUKDA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>9 - PANCHAVATI HOTEL RAMDEV, NEHRU NAGAR &nbsp;- (FAMOUS FOR MASALA PAV)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>10 - M K SWAMY, LOCATED AT CHURCH STREET CAMP - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN MAYONNAISE SANDWICH)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>11 - SHIVA PAN SHOP, RPD COLLEGE ROAD TILAKWADI - (FAMOUS FOR ICE PAAN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>12 - SAI DHABA,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;HONGA NATIONAL HIGHWAY 4 - (FAMOUS FOR EGG CHILLY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>13 - ALL INDIA BHEL HOUSE, LOCATED AT COLLEGE ROAD KELKAR BAGH - (FAMOUS FOR BUTTER PAPDI CHAAT)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>14 - KALYANI SWEETS, LOCATED AT GAVLI GALI CAMP - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>15 - MARAKEESH, MARAKEESH SHAIKH CAMPUS, NEHRU NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR MAKRANA KABAB)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>16 - MAHVEER CANTEEN, CLUB ROAD, NEXT TO RBL BANK - (FAMOUS FOR POHE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>17 - AJANTA, HUNS TALKIES ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR KURMA PURI DAHI VADA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>18 - VAISHALI&rsquo;S KITCHEN, LOCATED AT KELAR BAGH - (FAMOUS FOR DAL KHICHDI)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(456, 14, 31, 742, 'Karnataka', 'INDIA', 'BELLARY', 'bellary-fort-171490_640.jpg', 'bellary-fort-171490_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Located on the eastern side of Karnataka State, Bellary city is bounded by Raichur district on the north, by Dharwad district on the west, Chitradurga and Davangere districts on the south and Anantapur, Kurnool districts of Andhra Pradesh on east. The city stands in the midst of a wide, level plain of black cotton soil. The name Bellary originates from the word Balari which refers to Goddess Durugamma, who had manifested herself in the town. Bellary is the headquarters of the district of the same name in the state of Karnataka. An industrial town consisting of 7 taluks, Bellary city stands in the midst of a wide, level plain of black cotton soil filled with granite rocks and hills which form a prominent feature of the city. &nbsp;The city is spread mainly around two huge rocky granite hills, the Ballari Hill and Kumbara Hill. These two hills are dominant features of the city, and are visible from every part of the city. It is also said as per the myths that while Rama was searching for Sita, met Sugreeva and Hanuman at a place near Hampi. According to history, this place has played significant role during Satavahanas, Kadambas, Chalukyas of Kalyana, Kalachuryas, Sevunas, and Hoysalas period.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Some of the major hotels in Bellary offer a remarkable blend of tradition and modernity as well as a comfortable stay. Accommodation in Bellary is easily available. Hotels, guesthouses and lodges of different kinds are available. One can choose between luxurious star hotels and low budget economy hotels.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Though there is an airport at Bellary, no international flights run from here. This domestic airport has flights to places like Goa and Bangalore that have international airports.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Tourists can access to any place in Karnataka from the Bellary Railway Station. Bellary is well connected by Rail to Bangalore, Raichur, Tirupati, Hubli, Guntakal, Vijayawada etc.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Bellary city is well connected by bus services to all major cities, towns and important cities of neighbouring states.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Bellary is linked with the rest of the state by a vast network of well connected roads. It is on National Highway 63 Ankola Gooty road.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - BELLARY - [FAMOUS FOR MEWA GHEWAR(SWEET DISH MADE OF FLOUR, GHEE, MILK, BUTTER, SUGAR AND ALMOND, PISTACHIO, SAFFRON AND GREENCARDAMOM) ; HOLIGE OR OBATTU (IS SWEET STUFFED ROLLED BREAD)]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(457, 14, 31, 742, 'Karnataka', 'INDIA', 'BIDAR', 'blackbuck-1748173_640.jpg', 'blackbuck-1748173_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Bidar is a city that is located in the North Eastern part of Karnataka. The city is one of the cleanest cities in the state. It is also known as the peak of Karnataka. The history of the place makes the city popular among other cities of Karnataka. Since Bidar district shares the border with Andhra Pradesh, the city is close to some of the major cities of Andhra Pradesh like Hyderabad, than some of the cities in Karnataka itself. There are several tourist attractions in Bidar that flaunt the glorious past of the city. The best attraction of this place is Bidar Fort. An annual fair called the Bidarotsav is organised every year in the month of January or February. This festival showcases the culture and heritage of the city. This includes kite flying competitions, children&#39;s film festival, Mushairas or Sher recitals by renowned poets of the place, and street plays. Humnabad, which is very close to Bidar, is where a week&#39;s celebration of Veerbhadreshwara Jatra or the Chariot procession. This happens in February every year, and is considered one of the significant festivals of Bidar. Bidar is one of the coldest cities of Karnataka. The best time to visit the place is during monsoons as the city would be humid and warm during this season.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\nBidar offers variety of accommodations from economical and mid budget hotels to some luxury resorts providing with the best of all services and amenities 24X7. Other than private accommodation, one can also stay at hotels owned by the government.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Rajiv Gandhi International Terminal Begumpet Hyderabad serves as the nearest airbase to the city of Bidar lying about 140 kms away. The airport is quite busy and is well connected to many major cities of India. One can easily avail taxi from outside the airport till Bidar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Bidar is well connected to various cities of Karnataka by a network of well maintained roads. The district is also very easily approachable from certain parts of neighbouring states like Andhra Pradesh and Maharashtra via National Highway 9. Private buses run regularly to and from between Bidar city and other neighbouring cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The city of Bidar houses a railway station which is well connected to many other major cities of the country. Taxis are available outside the station to take tourists to the hotel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Bidar is a popular city immersed in history and religion. Taxi and bus are available mode of transportation in the city. One can also opt for auto rickshaws for short distance commutation. And if up for some short distance joy ride, cycle rickshaw is the mode of transportation.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - BIDAR - [FAMOUS FOR BELE PALYA(VEGETARIAN DISH MADE WITH LENTILS COOKED WITH VEGETABLES) ; BHAKRI IS A BREAD MADE OF JOWAR FLOUR ;&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(458, 14, 31, 742, 'Karnataka', 'INDIA', 'BIJAPUR', 'gol-gumbaz-1800569_640.jpg', 'gol-gumbaz-1800569_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Bijapur is the beautiful and historical district which lies in the Indian state of Karnataka. Historical attractions of the city are very famous where lots of travelers come all over the year. One can find Islamic architecture in the monuments of the city which reflects the historical heritage. Gol Gumbaz, Ibrahim Rauza, Jumma Masjid are most visited attractions of the city. Visitors can view about 50 temples, 20 tombs in the city. Reaching various sightseeing in the city is easy to reachable with the availability of various mode of transport. Krishna River is the main river which cuts through the city and covers the plain. Hand-woven traditional Ikal saris are very special items in the city market. The Bijapur travel guide will help you journey through this place. History of the city dates back to the 11th century. Chalukya dynasty founded this city during this period and called it as a Vijayapura. City was called as Vijapur or Bijapur in the 14th century during the dynasty of Bahamani sultanate of Gulbarga. In the 15th century, the Adil shah dynasty has taken the rule. He made many monuments during this period. After 1947, this district has become the part of Bombay state then reassigned to Mysore State. Finally in 1956 it comes under Karnataka. Best time to visit this city is winters as people can roam easily to various destinations. People also visit this district for getting adventurous experience.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Private hotels, lodges and PWD Rest Houses at reasonable rates are available. One can find various options to stay in this district. Tourists can get budget accommodation which is according to the pocket. Hotels of the city are well equipped with modern facilities and provide best hospitality services to their guest.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport is at Belgaum 205 kms from Bijapur. Indian and Jet airways flight operators connect Bijapur to the rest of India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - Bijapur is well connected by rail with Bangalore and other major cities of India. It has its own railhead that is located just 2 kms from the main town.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Bus</strong> - KSRTC buses ply regularly from nearby towns for Bijapur. It is well connected to other nearby cities and towns by roadways.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Bijapur is geographically connected by National Highway 13, National Highway 218 and other State Highways.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - BIJAPUR - [FAMOUS FOR SAARU(IS A SOUP PREPARED WITH CUMIN PEPPER, CORIANDER SEEDS AND TOMATO) ; ENNE-GAI(IS A BADANE KAAYI BULB STUFFED WITH PEANUT, SESAME, GINGER, GARLIC,GARAM MASALA, SALT AND SPICES) ; MOSARU BAJJI (IS A SALAD MADE FROM YOGURT) ; KEMPU KHAARA(CHUTNEY MADE WITH RED CHILIES) ; KAIPALYA(MADE FROM VEGETABLES), LAKU PALYA(LENTILS), BISI BELE BAATH(IS A RICED BASED DISH) ; SAJJAKADA HOLIGE, KARIGABADU, LADDU OF SEMOLINA AND BESAN, KARACHIKAYI,DURING THE FESTIVAL OF DEEPAVALI ; GODHI, HUGGI, HOLIGE, MODAKA, VERMICELLI, PAYASAM, SAJJAKA, JAWAR ROTI, MESTA BHAJI, RICE CURDS, PANCHAKAJJAYA, KARIGADABU AND GUDAGANA HUGGI ON THE OCCASION OF GANESH CHATURTHI ; HOLIGE, KARIGADABU, AND MANGO SHIKARANE ON &nbsp;BASAVA JAYANTHI(BIRTHDAY OF BASAVA) ; HOLIGE, KARIGADABU, VERMICELLI PAYASAM, BEVU BELLA AND GODHI HUGGI ON UGADI(IS KANNADIGA NEW YEAR CELEBRATED IN KARNATAKA) ; HOLIGE, JOWAR WADE AND, AND PUMPKIN GARGI ON THE FESTIVAL HOLI ; GODHI HUGGI, ALLITTU, BENGALI USALI, MOTH BEAN USALI AND HOLIGI ON THE OCCASION OF SHIVARATHRI]</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(459, 14, 31, 742, 'Karnataka', 'INDIA', 'CHAMARAJANAGAR', 'mountain-971349_640.jpg', 'mountain-971349_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Located in the leeward region of the Nilgiris, Chamarajanagar or Chamarajanagar is a town in Chamarajanagar district in the southern end of Karnataka state in India. The district is bordering Mysooru district to the west and north, Mandya and Bangalore districts to the northeast of Karnataka. Externally it borders Erode District of Tamil Nadu and Wayanad district of Kerala. The district was created after the larger Mysore district was split into the new Mysore district and the current Chamarajanagar district. The district capital is the city of Chamarajanagar. The taluks of Chamarajanagar include Chamarajanagar taluk, Yelandur taluk, Kollegal taluk and Gundalpet taluk. Chamrajnagar is a town located on the southern part of Karnataka. Named after the erstwhile king of Mysore, Chamraja Wodeyar IX, the place is on the highway that connects the state to Tamil Nadu and Kerala. The place was earlier named as Hari Kutara, and was later renamed as Chamrajnagar. There are a few tourist places in Chamrajnagar that are worth exploring. Most of the attractions here are religious, from which the place&rsquo;s religious orientation is evident. Some of the places of interest in Chamrajnagar include Masjidh-e-Fathima, an Ayyappa temple near the private bus station and an Eshwara temple. Since the place is closely knit to Mysore, one of the major festivals here is Mysore Dasara. Chamrajeshwara Chariot festival is another festival that takes place here in all its grandeur. &nbsp;The city is located around 65 kms from Mysore, and is well connected to the cities nearby by road, rail and air.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Chamarajanagar city offers Private hotels, lodges and PWD Rest Houses at affordable prices. Some of the attractions like the Bandipura Wildlife sanctuary do offer guests houses within the area. Do carry Light Cottons during summer time and Light Woollens during winters. Trekking equipments and binoculars can come in handy.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport from Chamarajanagar is 200 km away in Bangalore, from where one can take flights for most of the important cities in India. The airports at Coimbatore or Calicut are more distant but can be used for reaching Chamarajanagar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The city of Chamarajanagar has a railway station but the railway line lies on the Metre gauge line which runs from Mysore to Chamarajanagar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - There is a good network of interstate KSRTC buses that ply between Chamarajanagar and other important cities of the region and neighbouring states. Private and govt. buses run on a regular basis from Bangalore, Mysore or Coimbatore, Tamil Nadu.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - From Bangalore, the State Highway 17 can be used to reach Chamarajanagar via Mysore which is 65 kms from Mysore. The distance from Bangalore to Chamarajanagar is about 185 kms.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - CHAMARAJANAGAR - [FAMOUS FOR MANGALORE BAJJI ( IS A SNACK MADE FROM VARIOUS FLOURS AND CURDS) ; MANGALOREAN BANGUDE MASALA(MADE FROM MACKEREL FISH) ; &nbsp;MYSORE PAK (SWEET &nbsp;DISH MADE FROM GRAM FLOUR, GHEE) ; &nbsp;NEER DOSA(IS SNACKPRAPARED FROM RICE BATTER) ; &nbsp;OONDEES(IS A DISH MADE FROM SEMOLINA OR RICE) ; FOR JHUNKA (MADE FROM CHANNA DAL), &nbsp;JOLADA ROTTI( IS AN INDIAN BREAD MADE OF JOWAR), KARADANTU(IS A SWEET DISH MADE FROM EDIBLE GUM, DRY FRUITS, JAGGERY, NUT SEEDS), KOSAMBARI(SOUTH INDIAN SALAD MADE FROM PULSES AND SEASONED WITH MUSTARD SEEDS) ; BISI BELE BATH(IS A RICE BASED DISH) ; AJETHNA(IS A DRY GRAVYLESS VEGETABLES DISH CURRY), Bonda(IS A SPICY SNACK MADE FROM GRAM FLOUR BATTER, POTATO) CHITRANNA(IS ARICED BASED DISH]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(460, 14, 31, 742, 'Karnataka', 'INDIA', 'CHIKBALLAPUR', 'mountains-768557_640.jpg', 'mountains-768557_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Chikballapur is the district headquarters of the new Chikballapur district of Karnataka. This district, which was previously a part of Kolar district, has many fascinating tourist attractions. Chikballapur town lies about 50 kms from Bangalore and is the district headquarters of the Chikballapur district. This district is the birth place of the engineer Sri Visveswarayya, and is an educational centre, with many existing and proposed educational Institutions like the IIT Muddenahalli, The Visveswarayya Institute of Advanced Technology and the Sri Sathya Sai Baba University. Chikballapur has many natural attractions and manmade monuments that attract tourists here. The famous Nandi Hills is located in the Chikballapur Taluq. The Yoga Nandeeshwara Temple on top of the hill and the Bhoga Nandeeshwara Temple in the village at the base of the hill are the main attractions here. The Vivekananda Waterfalls, about 12 kms from Chikballapur town, is a beautiful place with the cascade at its best after rains. Rangasthala, which is also located near Chikballapur, has a beautiful temple with a splendid black stone Vijayanagara style statue of Lord Vishnu. Muddenahalli, which is also located near the region, is the hometown of Visveswarayya, and his house is now preserved as a museum. Some of the hills offer opportunities for rock climbing and mountaineering activities. Thanks to its proximity to the main city of Bangalore commute to Chikballapur is never a problem as there are many options available for tourists through road and rail.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are a few averages to modest hotels in and around the city. There are two hotels Rose Garden, Brindavan, Soumya and Shanti Sagar adjacent to each other, right across the National Highway 7.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Nearest airport to Chikballapur is the Bangalore Airport 38 kms from Chikballapur.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Chikballapur is located very near to Bangalore as a result there is plenty of public transport available. The buses run to and fro between Bangalore and Chikballapur all day and late night.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - There is a passenger train operating from Bangalore to Chikballapur however the frequency is very less.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Tourists can hire a private vehicle or a cab for an entire day. There are plenty of intra city buses and rickshaws to take one to the desired destination.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - CHIKMAGALUR - [FAMOUS FOR RAVA IDLI(MADE WITH SEMOLINA AND YOGURT AND SPICED WITH CASHEWNUTS, MUSTARD SEEDS, CHILLIES, GINGER AND CURRY LEAVES) ; UPMA(BREAKFAST DISH MADE FROM ROSTED SEMOLINA AND CHOPPED VEGETABLES ; &nbsp;AKKI ROTI (IS AN FLAT BREADMADE FROM RICE FLOUR BREAD) ; SAARU (A SOUP MADE FROM LENTILS, TOMATOES AND TAMARIND PULP) AND HULI (A LENTILS BASED DISH ALSO CALLED SOMBHAR)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - Pappu&#39;s Paanipuri Chat Centre, Basavanagudi Road, - [FAMOUS FOR AKKI ROTI, NENDRANGA CHIPS(BANANA CHIPS)]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - Town Canteen - [FAMOUS FOR KOSAMBARI(SOUTH INDIAN SALAD MADE FROM PULSES AND SEASONED WITH MUSTARD SEEDS)]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '');
