(461, 14, 31, 742, 'Karnataka', 'INDIA', 'CHIKMAGALUR', 'plantation-343915_640.jpg', 'plantation-343915_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Chikmagalur is a picturesque little town carved on the foothills of the Mullayanagiri range. This beautiful hill station is replete with breathtaking sights. It is located in the Chikkamagaluru district of the Indian state of Karnataka, at a distance of 250 kms from Bangalore. Chikmagalur district was formerly known as Kadur district. Big rivers like Tunga and Bhadra have their sources in the mountains of Chikmagalur. Chikmagalur district is also renowned for Mullayanagiri, the highest peak in the Karnataka. This beautiful place is dotted with waterfalls, hill stations and historical temples. It also boasts of a vibrant biodiversity which makes this region a popular weekend paradise. The word Chikmagalur has its own history. It is derived from the word Chikmagalur Uru which literally means younger daughters town in the native Kannada language. According to a local legend, it was given as dowry by the chief of Sakrepatna namely Rukmangada to his younger daughter. It was in Chikmagalur that the coffee was first cultivated in India by Babu Budan, a Muslim saint who came from Yemen in 1670 and started to grow coffee here. The region is popular as it has a huge number of tourist spots. The town of Chikmagalur lies near the Malnad region, the hilly wetlands of the state. It is said to have been gifted as dowry to the younger daughter of a legendary chieftain here, and there is also a place called Hiremagalur, land of the elder daughter which is a part of the Chikmagalur district now.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Chikmagalur is a solitary place with lofty hills, magnificent waterfalls, religious places and many hill stations nearby. This place is a favourite among the tourists. There are a number of hotels situated here to accommodate the tourists. Most of the Chikmagalur hotels are homely offering a panoramic view of the city. Tourists will definitely enjoy a good time while being here. Chikmagalur has a good variety when it comes to staying options. It has a range of budget hotels and accommodation for all visitors. Most of the hotels in Chikmagalur are clean and well maintained.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Mangalore Airport, which is located around 113 kms away, is the nearest airport to Chikmagalur. The airport is well connected to flights from Chennai, Kolkata, Mumbai and other major Indian cities.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Chikmagalur is well connected to cities like Bangalore, Mangalore, Hubli and Hassan via state run buses and private luxury buses. There is regular KSRTC bus service between Bangalore and Chikmagalur.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The city does not have a railway station, so the nearest railway station is located in Kadur, at a distance of about 40 kms away. Tourists can take a taxi from Kadur railway station for Chikmagalur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Due to the hilly terrain, autos are not very reliable and jeeps or buses are frequently available for tours around the town.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - ANNAPURNA VEG HOTEL, LOCATED AT OPPOSITE KSRTC BUS STAND, KADUR - (FAMOUS FOR BUTTER PANEER MASALA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - TOWN CANTEEN, LOCATED AT SH 57, VIJAYAPURA - (FAMOUS FOR BUTTER MASALA DOSA AND COFFEE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - COFFEE BARN CAFE, LOCATED AT SH-57, TARIKERE ROAD, ALLAMPURA - (FAMOUS FOR VEG SANDWICHES, PASTA AND MILK SHAKES)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - NEW HANCHIHULL COFFEE HUT,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT BYPASS ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;CHEESE SANDWICHES AND CARROT JUICE)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(462, 14, 31, 742, 'Karnataka', 'INDIA', 'CHITRADURGA', 'chitradurga-178075_640.jpg', 'chitradurga-178075_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Chitradurga is a town located in Chitradurga district of Karnataka. Belonging to the southern part of the state, the town has various other names like Chitradurg, Chittaldurg and Chitrakaldurga. The place derives its name from Chitrakaldurga which means picturesque castle Chitradurga is surrounded by valleys, huge rocks and boulders. The place has its mentions in Hindu scriptures like Ramayana and Mahabharatha. The archaeological traces of this place date back to 3rd millennium BC. Chitradurga is also popular for its stone fort Kallina Kote. The town is located around 202 kms to the northwest of Bangalore. Located at a distance of 200 kms from Bangalore town, Chitradurga city, in Chitradurga district of Karnataka lies in the heart of the Vedavati River valley and finds mention in the chronicles of the epic Ramayana and the Mahabharata. The city is recognized as the land of valour and chivalry and is surrounded geographically by Tumkur, Chikmagalur, Davangere and Bellary district and Ananthapur district of Andhra Pradesh state. Chitradurga gets its name from Chitrakaldurga, an umbrella shaped lofty hill located here. Chitradurga is a town full of history with its chain of lofty peaks and boulder strewn landscape, which is geologically supposed to be a part of the oldest rock formations in the country. Named after Chitrakaldurga, an umbrella shaped lofty hill found here, historically, Chitradurga was a part of the Vijayanagar kingdom. The area is also rich in many mineral deposits and has many gold and copper mines. The fort and ancient structures are a witness to the life and struggles of the kings who ruled from here for many centuries. Besides the fort, which is a major tourist landmark in Chitradurga, there are a few temples and picnic points that can give a break from the intense history session.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are a lot of options when it comes to accommodation in Chitradurga. Chitradurga offers a variety of luxury hotels, budget hotels, home stays, guest houses and service apartments at reasonable rates.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Bangalore which is about 200 kms from Chitradurga is the nearest domestic and international Airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Chitradurga has its own railhead. There are many trains that pass through Chitradurga.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - All Buses towards Bangalore pass through Chitradurga. There are good KSRTC and Private Volvo buses to Chitradurga every 5 minutes. There are buses from Davanagere and Shimoga to Chitradurga.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Chitradurga is situated in the heart of Karnataka state and therefore it is very well connected by road to most of the major cities in the state. Two National Highways, NH 4 and NH 13 intersect at Chitradurga. Tourists can comfortably drive from Davanagere to Chitradurga.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - CHITRADURGA - (FAMOUS FOR HAPPALA IS A SNACK MADE FROM LENTILS, BLACK GRAM, CHICKPEAS AND RICE FLOUR)</p>\r\n', ''),
(463, 14, 31, 739, 'Haryana', 'INDIA', 'DAVANAGERE', 'AA38.jpg', 'AA39.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Davanagere is famous for its well known delicacy Benne Dosa. Most people in Karnataka know about Davanagere through this dish. Folklore says that the city of Davanagere or Davangere was founded when one of the Chalukhya rulers made a pit stop here while on his journey. The king and his army were so thirsty and tired that they had to dig a lake to extract water. Thus, the region came to be known as Danivina Kere meaning lake for the thirsty folk. Later, the name changed into Davanagere. However, there is no lake or historical records to prove it. Some years ago, Davanagere was popular as the &#39;Manchester of India&#39; because of the flourishing cotton industries. Later, cotton industries saw a decline in the city. Still, Davanagere is a centre for agricultural products. Today, Davanagere is one of the interesting cities with several educational institutions. It has turned out to be an educational hub consisting of medical and dental colleges. Davangere has a blend of South Karnataka and North Karnataka cuisine. Don&#39;t forget to visit Sagar Benne Dose hotel and Ram &amp; Co. in Davangere. Durgamma Devi fair is one of the major events in Davangere. Durgambika Devi is one of the local deities of the region and it is said that the fair is conducted to pray for the rains. The fair happens around the Durgambika Devi Temple. Davanagere is a district in Karnataka which was once famous for its cotton mills. The city has a lot of attractions in an around it to be visited.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Accommodation in Davangere is easily available. One can find modest small budget and big hotels and guesthouses to spend a couple of days. However, tourists may expect good service, delicious food and comfortable stay at the accommodation.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Davangere does not have any airport. The nearest airport is at Hubli 132 kms from Devangere and the nearest International airport is at Bangalore at a distance of 320 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Davangere Railway station is located in the heart of the city and is connected to Miraj, Bangalore and Mysore by regular trains.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - There are many buses both KSRTC (Government owned) and private buses which fly regular services to Davangere from many cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Davangere is located on National Highway 4 and is well connected to the major cities of Karnataka.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - DAVANAGERE - [FAMOUS FOR KARA MANDAKKI (spiced puffed rice), UPPITTU(BREAKFAST DISH MADE FROM ROSTED SEMOLINA)]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - Bikaner Paratha Centre - (FAMOUS FOR BRINJOL BHAJJI, CHILLY BHAJJI, YELLU HOLIGE)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(464, 14, 31, 742, 'Karnataka', 'INDIA', 'GADAG', 'bullock-cart-172260_640.jpg', 'bullock-cart-172260_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Gadag is a unique district located in the western part of northern Karnataka. The district is bounded by six districts namely Dharwad on west, Belgaum on the northwest, Bagalkot on the north, Koppal on the east, Bellary on the southeast and Havari on the southwest. The Malaprabha River in the north and Tungabhadra in the south form the natural boundaries. Gadag and its sister city Betageri have a combined city administration, and the municipality of Gadag Betageri is spread over an area of 54.56 sq kms. According to the inscriptions Gadag was derived from Galadug, Kaladurga, Karedurga, Karthuka and Kritapur. The Rastrakutas, Chalukyas and Vijayanagara dynasty ruled the city. Gadag developed as a separate political and commercial centre since the period of Rashtrakutas. Gadag district is around 480 kms northwest of Bangalore. Gadag was separated from Dharwad district in 1997. Gadag and its sister city Betageri have a combined city administration. Gadag consists of five taluks namely Gadag Betageri, Ron, Shirhatti, Naragund and Mundargi. A number of late Chalukyan monuments built during 11th-12th centuries in the city indicate its historic past. The Temple of Veera Narayana and Trikuteshwara are places of religious and historic importance. There are two main Jain temples dedicated to Parshvanatha Thirthankara and Mahaveeera.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Private Hotels, Lodges and PWD Rest Houses at reasonable rates are available. The basic facilities at Gadag hotels are TV and AC. Apart from all these basic requirements the hotels also provide some luxurious facilities to the guests as per their demand and choice.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Hubli Airport is the nearest domestic airport to Gadag, situated at a distance of about 64 kms. Gadag is located at 414 kms from the Bangalore International Airport that is connected to all the major cities of India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Gadag Junction is the nearest railway station to Gadag, situated at a distance of about 2 kms from the city centre. A small station, it links trains that run between Hubli and Guntakkal via Hospet.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Gadag is well connected to major cities of Karnataka, including Bangalore, Mysore and Mangalore, by several KSRTC and local buses. Many tourists prefer buses to travel to Gadag as these are affordable and convenient.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - MCC, B Block, Kuvempu Nagar - [FAMOUS FOR UNDI ARE(RAWA, BESAN, CHURMAI, SHENGA, SHEVIN, HESAR,KARANJI, KUCHIDA KADABU]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - GADAG - [FAMOUS FOR SWEETS ARE HOORANA HOLIGE(IS A PANCAKE, JAGGERY AND CHICKPEAS ARE USED AND THEN STUFFED WITH WHEAT FLOUR), &nbsp;MALPURI ALSO CALLED MAMU KI MALPURI (STUFFED WITH KOHA)]</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(465, 14, 31, 742, 'Karnataka', 'INDIA', 'GANGAVATHI', 'highway-204148_640.jpg', 'highway-204148_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">A wonderful and picturesque city in the state of Karnataka, Gangavathi is a municipal council in Koppal district. It is an important commercial centre and is situated close to Tungabhadra Dam. Hampi, famous for UNESCO World Heritage Site is situated at a distance of just 14 kms from Gangavathi. The city offers immense pleasure and an everlasting experience to its tourists. Gangavathi Travel Guide is full of references to the mesmerizing sceneries and serene spots. Vijayanagara Ruins, Stone Chariot, Virupaksha Temple, Ugra Narasimha, Archaeological Museum are the famous sightseeing places of this city. It is one of the commercial hubs in the entire Hyderabad Karnataka region, it is also known as a largest city in terms of area and population when compared to any towns within Koppal district. It is often known as Rice Bowl city of Karnataka.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are many medium to budget accommodation options in and around Gangavathi city with all basic facilities like internet, TV, AC, room service, etc.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest Domestic Airport is Koppal Airport, Koppal, roughly one hour drive from Gangavathi. The nearest International Airport is Bangalore International Airport, Bangalore, roughly six hour drive from Gangavathi.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - The nearest Railway station is Hospet Junction from Gangavathi which is located at a distance of 21 kms from the city. It is very well connected to all other cities in the state of Karnataka.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - The Karnataka State Road Transport Corporation (KSRTC) runs buses to chief towns and cities in Karanataka. Gangavati is connected by road to Hampi, Hospet, Bangalore, Hyderabad, Mantralayam, Hubli and Bellary.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - HERITAGE, LOCATED AT &nbsp;ILAHI COLONY, ISLAMPUR - (FAMOUS FOR ICECREAM)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - THE CHILL OUT, LOCATED AT HAMPI - (FAMOUS FOR MANGO SHAKE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - SANJU RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT SANAPUR - (FAMOUS FOR SOUTH INDIAN FOOD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - BELLARY PARADISE, LOCATED AT HAKKA BUKKA ROAD, MVS AREA, HOSAPETE - (FAMOUS FOR BIRYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - PREM FAST FOOD, LOCATED AT COLLEGE ROAD, HOSAPETE - (FAMOUS FOR MEETHI PARATHA AND ALOO PARATHA)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(466, 14, 31, 742, 'Karnataka', 'INDIA', 'GULBARGA', 'buddha-vihar-223461_640.jpg', 'buddha-vihar-223461_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Gulbarga city is located in the north eastern part of the Indian state, Karnataka. The meaning of the name of the place is too lively. Gul means flower and berg means leaf thus making Gulbarga, a place of lavish living. The name of the place is in Persian language. The city has a glorious religious and historical past that attract the tourists to get to know about the rich past and heritage. The city has various temples and rich heritage that encourages the travellers to explore and get amazed with it. The well carved temples of the place attract a number of travellers and allow them to gaze upon its beauty. Along with the scenic beauty the tranquillity of the place is also very amazing. The look of the temples and their history makes tourists feel good. Khwaja Bande Nawaz Dargah holds a religious importance at the place that is appreciated by the tourists of the place. Gulbarga is also known for its unique cuisine. Jolada rotti is one of the staple food items here. Hoorana Holige is a sweet dish that is generally prepared only during festivals and other special occasions. Malpuri is another dessert that can be availed at sweet shops here. Throughout the region of Gulbarga, the climatic pattern is the same as most of the places in Karnataka.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are numbers of budget hotels at the place is available for the people that carries all basic facilities that includes, TV, AC, heater, etc. The budget hotels of the place try to fulfil all demand of their guests so that they feel comfortable. Apart from the facilities the cuisines at the hotels also have good taste that makes the travellers amazing.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The Gulbarga airport is well connected with all major cities so travellers can easily reach the place. Travellers can land and take off for various places as there are a number of flights that are available. The airfare for the place is affordable in range. The journey till the place is more comfortable and less time consuming by the airways.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The Gulbarga railway station is well connected with all major cities and towns of the place. Tourists can reach the place smoothly as there are a number of trains that run to all major cities. The rail fare is affordable for tourists.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Gulbarga is connected via Karnataka State Road Transport Corporation (KSRTC) bus service to other cities and villages.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Auto rickshaws and public transport can be availed to commute between places in and around Gulbarga.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - GULBARGA- [FAMOUS FOR TAHARI(PREPARED BY ADDING THE MEAT TO THE RICE) ; JOLADA ROTTI( IS AN INDIAN BREAD MADE OF JOWAR)]<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(467, 14, 31, 742, 'Karnataka', 'INDIA', 'HASSAN', 'temple-343930_640.jpg', 'temple-343930_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Hassan is the 4th largest city of Karnataka state and also the District headquarters of Hassan District. The scenic hill town of Hassan is located in the heart of Malnad and is about 195 kms from the capital city of Bangalore. Found by the chieftain Channa Krishnappa Naik in the 11th century, Hassan city is the headquarters of the Hassan district in Karnataka. Named after the local deity Hassanamba, this district is the architectural capital of Karnataka. The rich culture of the Hoysalas can be seen all over the district. The Hoysala dynasty ruled from Dwara Samudra the capital city then, between the 11th and 14th century. The ruins can still be found in and around Halebid in the Hassan district. Though the rulers of this dynasty belonged to the Jain faith, temples for Lord Shiva can be seen spread over the entire region. Well known for its historical values, Hassan now is city which has grown in leaps and bounds. It covers an area of 26 sq kms with a population of about 157000. The Hassan district falls under the Malnad and Maidan regions, and the entire district enjoys a beautiful climate. The city of Hassan experiences warm mornings and chilly and cold evenings. Though the official language here is Kannada, communication in English and Hindi is not uncommon. Hassan is easily accessible through road and rail and the city is well connected to other parts of the state. The Hassanamba Temple displays the local culture of the region in a grand manner and this is a popular destination among pilgrims and tourists alike.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Hassan is a popular destination and offers plenty of accommodation options. Star category hotels are few, but simple and decent hotels are available in plenty. Most of the hotels are conveniently located in the area near the bus stand. There are a host of low budget options with the circuit house inspection bungalow and the youth hostel.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - Hassan does not have an airport and the nearest airport is Bangalore from where one can take flights to other major destinations in India and abroad.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - Hassan is connected by rail to Bangalore, Mysore, Hubli, Shimoga and Mangalore.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Bus</strong> - One can get frequent Govt. buses to Hassan from Bangalore, Mysore and Chikmagalur and other nearby cities/towns.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Hassan is well connected to Bangalore, Mysore, Mangalore, Madikeri and Chikmagalur. It is around 187 kms from Bangalore and 115 kms from Mysore.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - HASSAN - [FAMOUS FOR RAGI &nbsp;ROTI(BREAKFAST DISH MADE FROM RAGI FLOUR), JOLADA ROTI(IS A TYPE OF BREAD MADE FROM JOWAR), AKKI ROTI(IS A RICE BASED DISH) AND CHAPATI ; &nbsp;HULI(LENTILS BASED DISH), MAJJIGE HULI(PREPARED FROM MILK CURD) ;BISI BELE BATH(IS A RICE BASED DISH), VAANGI BATH(MADE FROM VEGETABLES), CHITRANNA(IS A RICED BASED DISH) ; AVALAKKI(RICE BASED ADDING THE MILK); MANDAKKI(IS A PUFFED RICE DISH) ; NON VEGETARIAN DISH ARE CHICKEN AND MUTTON ; PALYA(IS APOTATO BASE DISH), KOSAMBARI(SOUTH INDIAN SALAD MADE FROM PULSES AND SEASONDED WITH MUSTARD SEEDS), BAJJI(IS SPICY SNACK MADE FROM GRAM FLOUR AND VEGETABLES)]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(468, 14, 31, 742, 'Karnataka', 'INDIA', 'HUBLI', 'dharwad-171625_640.jpg', 'dharwad-171625_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Hubli now called Hubballi is a famous tourist spot in Dharwad District of Karnataka. Hubli is also called Chota Bombay for being the commercial hub and important centre of commercial activities, Hubli is the twin cities of Hubli Dharwad which is located at a distance of around 420 kms north of Bangalore. The city of Hubli is just east of the famous Western Ghat and is surrounded by hills and lakes. Hubli is one of the most beautiful tourist and commercial centre of North Karnataka. It is home to some beautiful temples and historic monuments which attract tourists from all over the world. On your tour to Hubli Karnataka you can get to see the beautiful architectural marvels and designs which reflect the grandeur and splendour of yesteryears. It is a part of the twin cities of Hubli and Dharwad which is renowned for its textile units and rising industrial area which has a number of cotton and textile mills. In 1962 Hubli and Dharwad cities were combined together and was recognized as twin cities i.e. Hubli Dharwad Municipal Corporation. Hubli derives its name from the beautiful flower need Hu-balli, which is a Kannada word. It used to be the flower which decorated the entire Deccan Plateau. It is also called Hubballi and is a key producer of cotton and peanuts. Hubballi means flowering creeper which is a specific type of plant. This city is a commercial hub and a centre of commercial activities. It is located on the Western Ghats, surrounded by hills and lakes. Tourists love to visit this town to see its natural beauty. Temples and historic monuments of the city make it popular among tourists. Temples are beautifully crafted with architectural marvels and designs which attract the attention of people.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">People who are visiting this city will never have any problem of accommodation here. Hotels are well maintained and provide the best facilities to their guests. It is one of the largest cities of the state and has become one of the famous tourist destinations where lots of tourists visit all around the year. From luxury to budget hotels people can get various options to select and stay as per need and demands.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Hubli has its own airport located 18 kms away which connects the city well with rest of India. Direct flights to Hubli are available only from Bangalore.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>By Road</strong> - Frequent bus service to Hubli is available from neighbouring towns and cities of Karnataka. Both private and state transport buses ply to Hubli. Volvo buses, private buses and state owned NWKRTC buses ply regularly from these places for Hubli.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail</strong> - Hubli has its own station which connects the city to important places like Kolkata, Hyderabad, Bangalore, Chennai, etc. Plenty of trains to Hubli are also available from nearby towns at frequent intervals.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - HUBLI - [FAMOUS FOR GIRMIT(IS A SNACK MADE FROM PUFFED RICE, SPICY SEV, ONION TOMATO AND GREEN CHILLIES) ; JOLADA ROTI(MADE FROM JOWAR FLOUR), BADANIKAI PALYA(IS A VEGETABLE CURRY) ; &nbsp;MIRCHI VADA IS SNACK PREPARED BY COVERING BIG CHILLY WITH GRAM FLOUR AND DEEP FRYING IT) ; DHARWADA PEDA(IS SWEET DISH, IT IS A COMBINATION OF MILK, KOHA AND SUGAR)]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(469, 14, 31, 742, 'Karnataka', 'INDIA', 'COORG (KODAGU)', 'coorg-543854_640.jpg', 'coorg-543854_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\nCoorg or Kodagu is one of the popular tourist destinations in Karnataka. Coorg, which is situated in the south western part of Karnataka in the Malnad area of Western Ghats, is primarily a mountainous district that lies at a varied altitude of 900 mts to 1715 mts above sea level. Coorg is aptly termed as the Scotland of India and the Kashmir of Karnataka. The place is famous for its evergreen forests, lush green valleys, misty hills, sprawling coffee plantations, tea estates, orange groves, lofty peaks and fast flowing streams. It is a popular weekend getaway in Southern India, especially for people from neighbouring Dakshina Kannada, Hassan and Mysore districts of Karnataka and Kannur and Wayanad districts of Kerala. Coorg offers a magnificent old world charm which is reflected in its sleepy towns. Tourists to Coorg can experience a laidback and relaxing ambience and enjoy a slow paced life owing to the picturesque surroundings that offer breath taking views of both the eastern and western slopes of the Western Ghats. Excellent opportunities for outdoor activities like trekking, golf, angling and river rafting can be chosen here. Most of the trekking trails in Coorg are located in the Brahmagiri Hills of the Western Ghats. The Upper Barapole River, situated in the Brahmagiri Hills towards the south of Coorg, is the destination of water sports enthusiasts whereas Valanoor, the backwaters of River Kaveri, is the favourite destination of avid anglers. November to April is the most suitable season to visit Coorg. The scenic hill station of Coorg is also famous for its unique culture and traditions. Huttari, Mercara Dasara, Keil Podu and Cauvery Sankramana or the Thula Sankramana is some of the festivals celebrated in Coorg. The local cuisine, especially the non vegetarian dishes, is very famous amongst the various South Indian cuisines. Coorg is internationally renowned as a prominent coffee producing centre and the place experiences a typical tropical climate. It was the British who introduced coffee plantations to Coorg. Arabica and Robusta are the major coffee variants that are cultivated here. This place is also famous for its honey, cardamom, pepper and orange production.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Coorg being one of the popular tourist destinations offers widw range of accomodation facilities ranging from luxury to budget with all the modern ameneties and services.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport to Coorg is Mangalore International airport, which lies at a distance of 165 kms from Coorg. From here on tourists can take a cab to reach Coorg.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Coorg is well connected by road from the main cities of South India. Tourists can catch deluxe KSRTC buses to Coorg from Mangalore, Bengaluru and Mysore.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Nearest railway station to Coorg is Mysore at a distance of 95 kms. Tourists can hire a taxi from Mysore to reach Coorg. Alternatively, one can also hop on a bus which runs from outside the railway station to Coorg.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Commuting within Coorg</strong> - Public transport in Coorg is not very effective and it is preferable for tourists to hire rickshaws or cars. Cycling is also a frequent way of transportation for the sports enthusiasts.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(470, 14, 31, 742, 'Karnataka', 'INDIA', 'MANDYA', 'bicycle-166869_640.jpg', 'bicycle-166869_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Mandya is a small town located in Mandya District to the south east of Karnataka, while it shares it boundaries with Hassan, Mysore, Bangalore and Tumkur. Named after the Sage Mandavya, the landscape is interspersed with hills and has five rivers flowing though it Cauvery and its four tributaries, Hemavathi, Shimsha, Veeravaishnavi and Lokapavani. Coconut trees line the river banks and lush green forests provide a varied flora and fauna, making Mandya a picturesque tourist destination. Mandya is about 90 kms from Bangalore, which was initially a part of Mysore district. Mandya district came into existence on 1st July 1939 as it had its own cultural, religious and historical background. There are many places of attraction in and around the district but horde temples make it an important place of tourism. Agriculture is the main occupation of people in the district. Most of the industries that are run in the district depend on agriculture for their raw material. Sugar Mills, Jaggery making units, Rice Mills are the prominent industries of this district. It is believed that the name Mandya may have originated from the popular belief that Mandavya a holy sage lived in the area in ancient times.</p>\r\n', '<p>Private hotels, lodges and Rest Houses at reasonable rates are available here at Mandya.</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - Bangalore is the nearest airport about 90 kms from Mandya.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - Mandya is well connected with cities like Bangalore, Mysore, Shimoga, Chennai, Tirupati, Tanjavore, Tuticorin and Delhi through regular trains.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Bus </strong>- State run KSRTC buses and luxury buses ply Mandya and other important cities of Karnataka.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Mandya is about 90 kms from Bangalore, on Bangalore Mysore State Highway 17. There is a good network of roads that connects Mandya to other important cities of the region.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - MANDYA - [FAMOUS FOR BELE PALYA(VEGETARIAN DISH MADE WITH LENTILS COOKED WITH VEGETABLES)]<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(471, 14, 31, 742, 'Karnataka', 'INDIA', 'RAICHUR', 'krishna-river-172531_640.jpg', 'krishna-river-172531_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Raichur is capital town of the district of Raichur in Karnataka State. Situated in the north western part of Karnataka, the town of Raichur lies along the banks of River Tungabhadra and is known for its rich historical past. Raichur city has quite a few origins. Some say that the name was derived from that of Naichur. Some say that it was formed after merging two names that of Racha and Oor in Kannada which meant City of Kings during the Hoysalas. Raichur is one of the most exquisite tourist destinations in Karnataka, India. Raichur had imbibed the culture of many dynasties like the Mauryas, Cholas, Chalukyas and also the Bahmani and the Vijayanagar Empire, and has become the cultural Kaleidoscope. Raichur is also known as the town of two rivers. Situated along the River Tungabhadra and the River Krishna, Raichur is historically alluded to as Doab, and the word in Hindi means Two Rivers. Today, Raichur has transformed into an important commercial, industrial and educational centre besides being the headquarters of Raichur district. Famous for its produce of rice, oilseeds and cotton, the place is a commercial centre on the Central Railway.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Here in the city, travellers can spend beautiful vacations with their friends and family. There are numbers of famous hotels and resorts which are designed with latest designs that offer high class facilities and accommodation services to its guest. Here in the city, there are long list of hotels which are classified into various categories lie low budget hotels, cheap hotels and resorts and one can also find luxurious hotels. Tourists can select lodging option as per the budget.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - Hyderabad airport is about 200 kms and Bellary airport is about 145 kms from Raichur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - The Raichur Railway Station is an important station on the Guntakal Gulbarga railway line.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Bus</strong> - Raichur is well connected by a network of roads to important cities in India and within the state. Interstate buses are readily available from Raichur Bus Station.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Raichur is well connected by road to all the major cities in Karnataka and states.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - RAICHUR - [FAMOUS FOR SAJJA ROTTI(MADE OF BAJRA), JOLADA ROTTI( IS AN INDIAN BREAD MADE OF JOWAR) ; KOSAMBARI(SOUTH INDIAN SALAD MADE FROM PULSES AND SEASONED WITH MUSTARD SEEDS) ; PALLYA(MADE FROM FRIED VEGETABLES WITH A BIT URAD AND CHANNA DAL)]&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(473, 14, 31, 742, 'Karnataka', 'INDIA', 'RAMANAGARAM', 'BBBB.jpg', 'BBBB5.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Ramanagaram the Silk City is situated about 50 kms to the southwest of Bangalore and this place is the headquarters of the Ramanagara district. As is the case with the other parts of Karnataka this was also ruled by the Gangas, Cholas, Hoysalas and the Mysore Kings, but the city shot to fame with the shooting of the film Sholay during the 70&#39;s. Because of the city&#39;s rich harvest of silk, it is also often called the Silk City. Mysore silk saris that are famous all across the globe are weaved using the silk from Ramanagaram. Nature lovers will be happy here as the hills are home to yellow throated bulbuls and long billed vultures, which are endangered. The place is home to the Janapada Loka, a place for the folk art and culture of Karnataka. With many hills around, the place is a haven for rock climbers and this has contributed positively to tourism in the region. Ramnagaram with its lush green surroundings and popular tall granite hills is a famous tourist spot. Ramanagara is also known as the Silk Town and Silk City as it is a very important place for production of silk. The silk produced here forms the input for the famous Mysore Silk. Ramanagara is also famous for its Ramdevarabetta Vulture Sanctuary where one can spot critically endangered vultures in their natural habitat. Savandurga is a nearby hill and is also very popular among tourists. Janapada Loka is an organization here which has been very influential in promoting various art and cultural forms including dance and music.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Ramanagaram offers decent accommodation options for visitors. Although nothing extravagant but one can choose from good beach resorts, budget or mid range hotels, guesthouses and beach huts.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Instead of Ramanagaram tourists can a get flight to Hindustan Airport on regular basis. The airport is situated at a distance of about 48 kms from Ramanagaram.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Ramanagaram has its own railway station but it is not connected with major cities. Bangalore Railway Station is the nearest major railhead to Ramanagaram, situated at a distance of about 48 kms from the destination.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Ramanagaram does not have a bus stand. Nearest option is Channapatna. Ramanagaram is easily accessible by buses as state owned and private buses for the city are easily available from Bangalore and Mysore.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Tourists can hire cabs in Ramnagaram. There are various car rentals and cab bookings available.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - RAMANAGARAM - (FAMOUS FOR RASAM (IS A SOUP &nbsp;MADE FROM LENTILS, TOMATO AND TAMARIND PULP) ; JOLADA ROTI(IS AN INDIAN BREAD MADE FROM JOWAR) ; KESARI BATH(SWEET DISH MADE FROM SEMOLINA) ; MYSORE PAK (SWEET &nbsp;DISH MADE FROM GRAM FLOUR, GHEE) ; BISI BELE BATH(IS A RICE BASED DISH), KOSAMBARI(SOUTH INDIAN SALAD MADE FROM PULSES AND SEASONED WITH MUSTARD SEEDS)]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(474, 14, 31, 742, 'Karnataka', 'INDIA', 'RANEBENNUR (HAVERI)', 'fort-696157_640.jpg', 'fort-696157_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The town of Haveri is one of the places which give the authentic feel of North Karnataka. The history, culture and traditions are unique and interesting to explore. Haveri town is the district headquarters which forms the major part of the region. We can see a number of temple architectures as Haveri was one of the territories under the Western Chalukhyas. It is said that the name Haveri was derived from two Kannada words Havu-snake and keri-place, the land of snakes. This stronghold of the Western Chalukhyas is now a famous trading centres for Byadagi Menasinakayi the Red Chillis and cardamom garlands. Haveri is also an exciting place for heritage lovers as there are many ancient structures. The town of Haveri is surrounded by tourist places and religious sites. Utsav Rock Garden, Siddeshwara Temple, Kaginele, Galageshwara Temple, Bankapura Peacock Sanctuary, etc. are some of the prominent tourist places near the town of Haveri.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There good places to stay in Haveri town. Places like Hitaishi Palace Hotel, Shiva Shakthi Palace and Hotel Adarsha Deluxe are within 1 kms of the bus stand.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Hubli Airport which is around 80 kms from Haveri is the nearest airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Haveri Railway Station is one of the main railway stations with rail routes connecting to all major places in the state.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - KSRTC buses are available from places like Bengaluru, Davangere, Hubli and Dharwad on a regular basis. Haveri is connected through NH 47 from Bengaluru via Tumkur and Davanagere.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - KATEWADI DHABA, LOCATED AT PB ROAD, KIADB AREA - (FAMOUS FOR NORTH INDIAN FOOD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - BASAVARAJIAH KHANAVALI, LOCATED AT VAGEESH NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR JOLADA ROTTI IS A TYPE OF BREAD MADE FROM FLOUR)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - ASHOK BHAVAN, LOCATED AT DODDAPET - (FAMOUS FOR DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - GAJA S S BIRIYANI POINT, LOCATED AT GUTTAL BUS STAND RD, DODDAPET - (FAMOUS FOR MUTTON AND CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - GHAR DHABA, LOCATED AT NH SERVICE ROAD, KUNABEV - (FAMOUS FOR AALU FRY WITH CURD AND PALAK PANEER WITH TANDOORI ROTI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - SHIVA DHABA, LOCATED AT MAKANUR - {FAMOUS FOR MADKI MASALA (MOAT GRAM) WITH ROTI AND RICE JEERA (CUMIN)}</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(475, 14, 31, 742, 'Karnataka', 'INDIA', 'KOLAR (ROBERTSON PET)', 'plateau-204204_640.jpg', 'plateau-204204_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The quiet little town of Kolar lies in the eastern edge of Karnataka. Spread over an area of 3969 sq kms, Kolar borders Tamil Nadu as well as Andhra Pradesh, thus earning it the sobriquet of the Eastern Gateway to Karnataka. Kolar is today famous for its gold mines but it has a golden past as well a past that has given the town some truly magnificent temples and fortresses. One of the myths and legends that revolve around Kolar is that it was the abode of Valmiki, the ancient saint. Lord Ram visited him in Kolar after his exile and it was here where Goddess Sita stayed when Lord Ram banished her from his life. Their sons Luv and Kush were born in Valmiki&#39;s ashram at Kolar. The warrior saint Parasuram reportedly lived in the green hills that fringe the western side of Kolar. As far as recorded history is concerned, Kolar&#39;s name is evocative of its past. Kolar is derived from the word Kolahapura which means violent city. The hills of this cool little town have seen violent battles between the Cholas and the Chalukya dynasties. The remains of this glorious past can still be witnessed in the town. The Kolaramma and Someswara temple are worth visiting. Other popular activities for visitors include adventure sports like parasailing and rock climbing. Kolar is located 65 kilometres from Bangalore and is well connected by rail and road. July to September is considered as the ideal time to visit Kolar.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\nThere are a number of hotels for accommodation in Kolar that provide all the required facilities to the travellers. The basic facilities at Kolar hotels are TV and AC. Apart from all these basic requirements the hotels also provide some luxurious facilities to the guests as per their demand and choice.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Bangalore International Airport is the nearest airport to Kolar, catering to both domestic and international tourists. It is situated at a distance of about 62 kms from Kolar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Kolar has its own railway station, situated at a distance of about 2 kms from the city centre. The railway station is well connected to all the nearby cities and towns.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Kolar is a major city in Karnataka, which is well connected to various nearby cities and towns. Several private buses and the state owned KSRTC (Karnataka State Road Transport Corporation) buses ply regularly from Bangalore for Kolar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Kolar is well connected to all the major cities in Karnataka and neighbouring states via National Highway 4.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SNACKS POINT, LOCATED AT SH 95, M VISHWESHWARYA NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR MASALA PURI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - IDLY ZONE, LOCATED AT KAMAL MEDICALS, SWARNA NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR IDILY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - HOTEL NANDI UPAHAR, LOCATED AT KOLAR MAIN ROAD, SH5, AMPC COLONY, BANGARAPET - (FAMOUS FOR PAROTHA, SAMBHAR,RASAM)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - B.G.T RAVI BIRYANI HOTEL, LOCATED AT NEAR BALAMURGAN TEMPLE,CORNATION ROAD,BANGARPET TALUQ - (FAMOUS FOR MUTTON BIRYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - BACK CANTEEN, LOCATED AT SMITH ROAD, BAND LINE COLONY, NETHAJI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR NOODLES AND PASTA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n6 - NAVYA, LOCATED AT 5TH CROSS ROAD, 2ND BLOCK, SWARNA NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR PANI PURI)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(476, 14, 31, 742, 'Karnataka', 'INDIA', 'SHIMOGA', 'rain-forest-1401155_640.jpg', 'rain-forest-1401155_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Adventure, sacred, Trek in the nature&#39;s lap with hills, lakes, rivers and valleys all your way, in a package makes a perfect holiday destination to be. With all the potential tourist hot-spots Shimoga makes an enviable tourist destination in Karnataka State of India. Shimoga in Shimoga district of Karnataka has a blend of small town charm and cosmopolitan city. Adorned with wide spread meadows, hillocks covered with thick forest with some exclusive flora and fauna, going hand in hand with many remarkable religious places, Shimoga offer delight to every visitor from all walks of life. Shimoga, formerly called as Shivamogga meaning the Nose of Lord Shiva, is centrally located in Karnataka, on the banks of Tunga River. The city lies in Malnad region of Shimoga district, Karnataka with a population of about 2 lakh denizens who are basically engaged in agriculture. A common feature you find in almost every house in and around Shimoga are the slant roofs of the houses. This is obviously because the District of Shimoga receives more rainfall in rainy season. The climate in this city with a small town charm is always pleasant. Shimoga is not a place to be visited in a hurry. Shimoga, literally meaning &#39;The Face of Shiva&#39;, is a city that lies at a distance of about 275 kms from Bangalore. A part of the Malnad area as the locals call it, it lies straddling the Western Ghats and is well connected by road and rail to other towns and cities in the state, enabling easy travel. With five major rivers flowing through the district, the Shimoga region is very fertile and is called the &#39;bread basket of Karnataka&#39; and the &#39;rice bowl of Karnataka&#39;. The Sahyadri range keeps the rivers well supplied with ample rainfall almost perennially. Locals call Shimoga Heaven on Earth as it offers something for everyone. It has temples, hills, lush vegetation and the famous Jog falls here is the highest waterfall in India.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Shimoga is a place which is dotted with tourist attractions in huge numbers. To accommodate tourists, the place houses several luxury hotels to mid range and budget hotels and guest houses. While the luxury accommodations offers as many facilities and amenities as possible to make the stay comfortable, the other budget places are also quite good and offer impeccable service.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport to Shimoga is Mangalore Airport situated around 190 kms away. One can hire a taxi from the airport to the town. Also an airport is to be launched at Soggane by year 2017 which lays just 13 kms from Shimoga.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Shimoga is a district which is well connected to its neighbouring cities via good network of roads. Bus services owned by KSRTC and other private owner plies regularly between the cities connecting Shimoga to Bangalore, Mangalore, Mysore, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - With a railway station of its own, Shimoga district is well connected to many major cities of the country. A regular rail service also connects the region to Bangalore directly which is 280 kms away.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Shimoga as a town is a small place which also serves as the district headquarters. Commuting with the city is quite easy with taxis, although one might want a guide to explore the place. Auto rickshaw is other option which charged minimum of Rs. 20 for commuting from one city to another. However, bargaining might come as a useful tact.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SHIMOGA - [FAMOUS FOR MIDIGAYI IS IS A PICKLE MADE FROM MANGO) ; PAAYASA (SWEET DISH MADE FROM BOILING RICE, BROKEN WHEAT, TAPIOCA OR VERMICELLI WITH MILK AND SUGAR) ; THAMBLI IS ATYPE OF CURD PREPARE FROM INGREDIENTS LIKE TURMERIC ROOT,GINGER, ROSE SPROUTS AND JASMINE) ; &nbsp;GENESALE IS SWEET DISH MADE FROM COCONUT RICE AND JAGGERY ; HALASINA HANNINAKADUBU IS SWEET DISH MADE FROM JACKFRUIT ; CHIROTI (IS SNACK MADE FROM MAIDA AND DREEP FRIED IN GHEE)]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '');
