(491, 14, 31, 752, 'Rajasthan', 'INDIA', 'DHOLPUR', 'india-842021_640.jpg', 'india-842021_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Dholpur is a famous holiday destination in the state of Rajasthan, which is popularly known for Damoye waterfalls in Sarmathura. Earlier called Dhawalgiri, this place was later known as Dhaulagir and finally Dholpur. This district is situated near Bharatpur District and is surrounded by the state of Uttar Pradesh in the north and Madhya Pradesh towards south. Yadavas controlled the entire region till the battle of Mahabharata concluded. The ancient history of Dholpur is reflected in the ruins of the fort situated on the banks of Chambal River. Ruins of Mahabharata period can also be seen at the ancient temple of Muchukund Ji. Dholpur was also once part of Matsya Janpada, which formed one of the 16 Maha Janpadas during Buddha&#39;s period. The Matsya Janpada later became part of the Mauryan Empire. Later on, during Gupta dynasty, it became part of Mathura Janpada. From 8th century to 10th century, the Janpada was ruled by Chauhans, after which it came under the reign of Jats. The town is believed to have earned its name from Raja Dholan Deo Tonwar, a ruler of this district. The king used to live at a place called Bilpur, which is situated near Chambal and features an old fort. In 1120 AD, the Dholpur Fort was constructed by Dharampal, who was the Raja of Karauli. During Mughal rule, Dholpur was a famous tourist spot, which was frequented by royals for its natural beauty and forests. The major attractions in and around Dholpur include Talab-e-Shahi, Machkund Temple, National Chambal Wildlife Sanctuary and Shergarh Fort. Part of the princely state before Indian independence, it became a separate district in 1982. The district comprises four tehsils, namely Baseri, Bari, Dholpur and Rajakhera. The town of Dholpur is situated between Gwalior and Agra that are 55 kms away from the main town. Among all the seasons, the best time to travel to Dholpur is the winter season, between October and February.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">In a tourist destination like Dholpur, there is no dearth of classy hotels and resorts for comfortable accommodations in the city. It has many hotels located within the city limits while the resorts are mostly located in the outskirts. These hotels and resorts in Dholpur offer superior accommodations along with immaculate services and amenities to make stay in the city comfortable. Resorts in the city offer a mesmerizing staying option in the midst of natural greenery and tranquillity.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The closest airport is at Gwalior, around 60 kms from Dholpur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Dholpur has own junction which linked all major places of Rajasthan as well as neighbouring state.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Dholpur is exactly located along the National Highway 3 running from Agra to Mumbai. Another National Highway 11B also passes through Dholpur. These national highways along with state roads connect Dholpur with all major cities of Rajasthan and neighbouring states of Uttar Pradesh and Madhya Pradesh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - There are Rajasthan State Road Transport Corporation (RSRTC) buses that ply to different parts in and around the district. State or private bus services are regularly available from all major places in the Rajasthan or also from neighbouring state.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - NARAYAN HALWAI, NEAR DHOLPUR BUS STAND - (FAMOUS FOR AALOO KI SABAZI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - ZAHID DA DHABA, LOCATED AT NATIONAL HIGHWAY - (FAMOUS FOR SARSON KA SAAG)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - MITTHAN HALWAI, AT SANTAR ROAD - [FAMOUS FOR JALEBI DHAI]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - AGARWAL SWEETS, LOCATED AT LAAL BAZAR - (FAMOUS FOR MILK CAKE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - BUNTY HALWAI, AT NEAR RAILWAY STATION - (FAMOUS FOR MANGO LASSI)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(492, 14, 31, 752, 'Rajasthan', 'INDIA', 'DUNGARPUR', 'india-1489024_640.jpg', 'india-1489024_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Nestled at the foothills of the Aravalis in the state of Rajasthan in India, the rural town of Dungarpur is famous for its architecturally marvellous temples and palaces. With the blue waters of the Gaibsagar Lake at its heart, and 2 magnificent rivers Mahi and Som flowing through the region, Dungarpur is a beautiful town that must be explored. Once a stronghold of the Bheels a tribe whose history of inhabitation in the Aravalli range is believed to date back to 4000 BC, Dungarpur was initially the village of Dungaria a Bheel chief. It is believed that Rawal Veer Singh assassinated Dungaria and established the town of Dungarpur sometime around 1282. The rulers of Dungarpur claim to be descendants of the Rajput house of Mewar. Dungarpur in Rajasthan features an amazing landscape. While on tours to Dungarpur Rajasthan, tourists will encounter the wild and rugged terrain in the northeast of the town on one hand, and the fertile plains of the southwest on the other. Besides, the scenic beauty of the town is further enhanced by the rivers Mahi and Som flowing through it. The landscape of Dungarpur in Rajasthan is dominated by teak, mahua, mango and khajur trees. Tours to Dungarpur Rajasthan will also provide opportunities to spot a wide variety of wildlife inhabiting the hills, including jackal, jungle cat, Indian fox, hyena, black faced monkey, porcupine, common mongoose, among others. One can also spot bird species like partridges, peafowl, quails, cuckoos, eagles, and vultures on Dungarpur tour.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are limited options for accommodation in Dungarpur. There are two hotels that are the most sought after here. Though there are plenty of options just inside the 50 kms radius from Dungarpur. One can find a lot of hotels in this range.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The Maharana Pratap Airport or Dabok Airport of Udaipur is the nearest airbase to Dungarpur. This airport is connected to major Indian destinations like, Delhi, Mumbai, Hyderbad, Jaipur, Jodhpur and Ahmedabad by frequent flights.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The nearest railway station of Dungarpur is situated in Ratlam of Madhya Pradesh. This station is well connected to major Indian destinations. Cabs can be booked from this station to Dungarpur at affordable prices.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Tourists can reach the destination by government buses from Udaipur. Private and luxurious buses are also available from nearby cities to Dungarpur.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - UNIQUE CAFETERIA, LOCATED AT ADARSH NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR CHOCOLATE SHAKE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - JAIN FAST FOOD, LOCATED AT ADARSH NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR SANDWICH WITH FRIES AND COLD COFFEE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - JODHPUR MISHTHAN BHANDER, LOCATED AT SHASTRI COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR PAAV BHAJI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - HARI OM FAST FOODS, LOCATED AT SUBHASH PARK, NEW COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR VADA PAO)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - BHAIJI, LOCATED AT IN FRONT OF STATE BANK OF INDIA, DUNGARPUR ROAD, KRISHNA NAGAR, SAGWARA - (FAMOUS FOR PARATHE)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(493, 14, 31, 752, 'Rajasthan', 'INDIA', 'GANGANAGAR', 'india-1463879_640.jpg', 'india-1463879_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Sri Ganganagar is the northern most and a planned city of the Indian state of Rajasthan situated near borders of Rajasthan, Haryana and Punjab states and the international border of India and Pakistan. It is the administrative headquarters of Ganganagar district. Nestled beautifully on the banks of the River Sutlej, Sri Ganganagar is located in the colourful state of Rajasthan in close vicinity to the Great Thar desert. It is situated near the borders of Rajasthan, Haryana and Punjab states and the international border of India and Pakistan. It is amid one of the biggest districts of Rajasthan and the administrative headquarters of Ganganagar district. Shri Ganganagar city guide is incomplete without a mention of the Laila Majnu ki Mazar, the famous lovers known in the Indian history, Hindumalkot, Gauri Shankar Temple and Balaji Dham. The city is widely known as the food basket of Rajasthan and green district of Rajasthan. Sri Ganganagar is subjugated by Punjabi civilization and is also famous as the Punjab of Rajasthan because the region was primarily inhabited by Punjabi Hindus and Sikhs. The name of the city is after Maharaja Shri Ganga Singh Bahadur who was the king of Bikaner. The major source of livelihood of locals derives from agricultural activity. Wheat, Guar, sugar cane, bajra and grams are the prime cash crops which are grown in the district.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Sri Ganganagar has some deluxe and many medium to budget accommodation options. The deluxe accommodation options have all basic facilities like internet, homely food etc.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest International Airport is Sri Guru Ram Das Jee International Airport, Amritsar, roughly four and a half hour drive from Sri Ganganagar. It is well connected to a spectrum of cities like Delhi, Srinagar, Surat and Mumbai.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Sri Ganganagar has its own Railway Station named as Ganganagar Railway Station which is connected to all the major cities of Rajasthan and other cities like Chandigarh, Delhi, Jaipur, Kanpur and Indore.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Sriganganagar is well linked with all the major areas of Sriganganagar. Many roadways and private buses are frequently available to major cities of north India like Delhi, Jaipur and Ajmer.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - MUNCHEEZ RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT E BLOCK - (FAMOUS FOR CHILLY PATATO)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - BIG BITE FAST FOOD RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT 16, VINAYAK VIHAR, OPPOSITE BIHANI PHARMACY COLLEGE - (FAMOUS FOR BURGER)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - NAGPAL MANGO BAR, LOCATED AT GOL BAZAAR, OLD DHAN MANDI - (FAMOUS FOR VARITIES OF SHAKES AND JUICES)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - YUMMY ROLLS, LOCATED AT NO. 15, P BLOCK - (FAMOUS FOR EGG ROLL)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n5 - AGRA CHAAT, LOCATED AT OLD DHAN MANDI - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;ALOO TIKKI, DAHI BHALE AND PAPDI CHAAT)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n6 - EAT WELL RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT OPPOSITE NISHANTH SINGH PETROL PUMP, &nbsp;SURATGARH ROAD, MOTOR MARKET - (FAMOUS FOR BUTTER CHICKEN)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n7 - SONI, &nbsp;LOCATED AT RAILWAY STATION ROAD, COLLECTORATE AREA, OLD DHAN MANDI - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n8 - PANDIT JI, LOCATED AT P BLOCK - (FAMOUS FOR CHHOLE KULCHE)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n9 - AMRIT MISTHAN, LOCATED AT SH3 RAVINDRA PATH, B BLOCK&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA, DHOKLA, ICECREAM AND KULFI)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(494, 14, 31, 752, 'Rajasthan', 'INDIA', 'HANUMANGARH', 'india-1034829_1280.jpg', 'india-1034829_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Nestled beautifully on the banks of the River Ghaggar, Hanumangarh is located in the colourful state of Rajasthan. It was formerly called as Bhatner as it was under the influence of Bhati Rajputs. The district includes seven Tehsils: Hanumangarh, Rawatsar, Nohar, Sangaria, Pilibanga, Bhadra and Tibbi. &nbsp;After being won by Raja Shardul Singh, the city was named as Shardulgarh. Hanumangarh is a town which is located on the banks of the river Ghaggar. This Hanumangarh town is also the administrative seat of Hanumangarh district. The formation of this beautiful town of Hanumangarh too is quite significant. As per the records of the historians, the town of Hanumangarh was the empire of Bhati Rajputs and therefore its former name was Bhatner. There was an ancient Bhatner fort that is located in the centre of the town of Hanumangarh. It is about nine hundred years So much so that in the Aaine Akbari, mention has been made of this fort. A renowned Bhadrakali temple can also be found near the city on the banks of River of Ghaggar River. Exquisite works of art and architecture too can be found in the nearby areas of the area Hanumangarh. All these are quite old. Quite a number of terracotta tiles for decoration are found in the late Kushana style. Few more coins too are also been found. There are other things that too are being excavated from the region. For example, two terracotta capitals having the depth of 15 inch from the peak of the mound with stepped pyramids along their boundaries have also been found out.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Hanumangarh has some deluxe and many medium to budget accommodation options with all facilities to make your stay a memorable one.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest Airport from Hanumangarh is Chandigarh Airport, roughly five and half hour drive from the city. Chandigarh Airport is well connected to the major cities like Amritsar, New Delhi, Bangalore, Mumbai, Goa, Ahmedabad, Jaipur and Leh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- The town has its own Railway Station called as Hanumangarh Railway Station. It is well connected with other cities like Jalore, Jaipur and Agra.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- The Hanumangarh is attached with all foremost cities of Rajasthan thus tourists can effortlessly arrive to the town by road.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Several state transport and personal Buses coaches ply on the routes between these towns.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - MINAKSHI SWEET CORNER, LOCATED AT CHOLA PURI AND PANEER PAKODA - (FAMOUS FOR BHAGAT SINGH CHOWK,HANUMANGARH JUNCTION, DAL SINGH NAGAR)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - JUNEJA VALAYTI TADKA, LOCATED AT OPPOSITE BUS STAND, IN FRONT OF CITY HEART HOTEL JUNCTION, DURGA COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(495, 14, 31, 752, 'Rajasthan', 'INDIA', 'JALORE', 'rajputs-67609_640.jpg', 'rajputs-67609_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Situated on the southern edge of the vast sandy plain of Marwar, is a delightful city of Jalore. It is a typical small Rajasthani town where the hustle and bustle of the bigger cities is missing. It is surrounded by Barmer on the Northwest, Sirohi on the Southeast, Pali on the Northeast and Banaskantha district of Gujarat on the Southwest. Jalore lies south of Sukri River a tributary of Luni River and is about 121 kms south of Jodhpur. The serene and unruffled surroundings make Jalore a good place to experience the unspoiled and friendly atmosphere of rural Rajasthan. The city is also known as the Granite City with hoards of shops dealing in granite. Jalore is a historical place located on the banks of River Sukhi in Rajasthan. In ancient times, the city was known as Jabalipura. During 9th century, the city gained its glamour and was flourished with constructions of several structures. The Jalore fort is located on the hillock called Songir is the major tourist attraction. The region was ruled by both Hindu and Muslim rulers, hence one can see the different influences throughout the city. Jalore fort is one of the living testimonies for the architectural brilliance of ancient era. This is one of the popular tourist destinations in Rajasthan and said to be impregnable. The mosque, Hindu temple and Jain temple are located inside the fort is the unique feature of Jolore fort. The entire region is filled with variety of Jain temples which are built in varying period. Malik Shan Mosque and Sire Mandir are two important spots in Jalore. Topekkana is a cannon building which is another tourist attraction and worth to visit.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Jalore being a major attraction of the state has so many hotels, and guest houses which offer a place to stay to visitors and travellers. Hotels in Jalore ranges from reasonable ones to deluxe one and one can avail according to their budgets. Hotels of Jalore also offer guide facilities to their customers which will take to all the sights of Jalore.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Nearest Airport is Jodhpur Airport 141 kms from Jalore. At Jodhpur one can find nearly all type of domestic flights.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Jalore has its own railway station and fairly served by trains. Jalore is situated in Samdari Bhildi narrow-gauge segment which is under conversion to broad-gauge shortly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- National Highway 15 passes through the district in Sanchore tehsil. All the block head quarters are connected with bus routes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - There are good numbers of buses available to reach nearby cities like Udaipur, Jodhpur and Jaisalmer of Rajasthan.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - BAJRANG, LOCATED AT GUDAMALANI - BAGORA - SAYALA - JALOR - BHINMAL RD, SURYA COLONY, MUDTRA SILI - (FAMOUS FOR VADA PAV)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - KHETESHWAR NASTA CENTRE, LOCATED AT SHIVAJI NAGAR COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR DOSA, SAMBHAR AND IDLI WADA)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(496, 14, 31, 752, 'Rajasthan', 'INDIA', 'JHALAWAR', 'temple-517529_640.jpg', 'temple-517529_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The city of Jhalawar is located on the south east of Rajasthan along the edge of Malwa plateau. Jhalawar is about 87 kms from Kota and 335 kms from Jaipur. Jhalawar is situated at an altitude of 312 mts above sea level. The name Jhalawar is derived from the former royal state of Jhalawar. Jhalawar means a house of Jhalas the Rajput&rsquo;s. A visit to the Jhalawar is assured to be a memorable experience. Most commonly used languages in Jhalawar are Hindi, Rajasthani and English. Jhalawar is a treasure house of forts, wildlife and cave paintings. Jhalawar is the administrative headquarters of Jhalawar District. Jhalawar was known as Brijnagar earlier. Jhalawar is founded by Zalim Singh in 18th century on the banks of the river Kali Sindh. The major exports from the Jhalawar are cotton, oil seeds and opium. Jhalawar has stony but water laden lush landscape. Winters are colourful and mesmerizing with Red poppy fields and orange laden. Jhalawar region contributes a major share of the production of Citrus. Jhalawar is located in the south eastern part of Rajasthan in Hadoti, also known as the land of Hadas. This district covers an area of 6928 km and is a part of the Kota Division. Jhalawar, also known as Brijnagar is the administrative headquarters of the district. The north eastern area of the district is bounded by Baran district while the south western part is bordered by the Kota District. Historically, the city of Jhalawar was founded in 1791 AD by Jhala Zalim Singh, who was the Diwan of the Kota district, back then. He had the vision of developing this place into a military cantonment so as to safeguard the region against the attack of Maratha invaders. Later, the British handed over the place to the grandson of Jhala Zalim Singh, named Jhala Madan Singh. He became the first ruler of the city of Jhalawar and ruled the place from 1838 to 1845. Tourists planning trips to Jhalawar may pay a visit to the historical Jhalawar fort. The fort is also known by the name Garh Palace. Jhalawar has a 100 ft high Surya Temple, dedicated to the Sun God. One can find magnificently carved sculptures inside the temple. The city is situated alongside the River Chandrabhaga and is bounded by walls from all sides.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Jhalawar has nice options for accommodation in the form of hotels, home stays and palatial hotels. There are options for all budget sizes. Accommodation available at Jhalawar includes deluxe hotels and economy hotels. Tourists can choose the accommodation as per their needs and budget.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The Kota Airport is the nearest Airport to Jhalawar, located at a distance of 82 km. It is connected to most of the major cities of India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Ramganj Mandi railway station, located at a distance of 25 kms is the nearest rail link to Jhalawar. The station is well connected to major Indian cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - National Highway 12 passes through Jhalawar which connects all major cities of Rajasthan to Jhalawar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - RSRTC Buses are available from all major cities of Rajasthan to Jhalawar. Both state owned and private buses connect the city of Jhalawar to various nearby cities like Bundi, Kota and Jaipur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Jhalawar is a small township and easy enough to get around on foot. But there are several auto rickshaws, cycle rickshaws and Tongas available for visiting surrounding transportation in Jhalawar.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SHRI PARSHWANATH NAMKEENS, LOCATED AT GHUR PURA MOHALLA - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORI AND SAMOSA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - BISMILLAH, LOCATED AT KAPIL VASTU COLONY, KHANDIYA - (FAMOUS FOR FRIED CHICKEN)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - MAHESHWARI RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT BUS STAND, JHALRAPATAN - (FAMOUS FOR DAL BATI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - JAIN KACHORI CENTRE, LOCATED AT JAWAHAR COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORI)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(497, 14, 31, 752, 'Rajasthan', 'INDIA', 'JHUNJHUNU', 'india-1463872_640.jpg', 'india-1463872_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Jhunjhunu is a town located in the Shekhawati region of Rajasthan. The town is widely popular owing to a large number of beautifully painted havelis present here. The major tourist attractions here are the 18th century Khetri Mahal, Bihariji Temple and Mertani Baori. The paintings inside the Seth Ishwardas Mohan Das Modi Haveli are among the best of their kind present in the Shekhawati region. The Tibrewala Haveli, which belongs to the 19th century, is famous for its coloured glass windows. Jhunjhunu is the cultural capital of the region known as Shekhawati and has a rich history, as it played a significant role in the politics of Shekhawati. If local legends are to be relied upon, the history of this place dates back to the Pandavas who, while wandering, had spent some time here. This region has been called the&#39; largest open art gallery in the world&#39;. Jhunjhunu is the district head quarters and ancient capital of Shekhawati, could be the most attractive places for the tourist. It has some of the most beautiful buildings, not to be missed by its visitors. Having the Aravali range to guard it on the southeast, the lush green valley also interests the tourists for its natural beauty. Every house has a story to tell, be it about their brave sons who have for years served the nation from the front or be it the temples and holy places in the town.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are hotels suiting all budget brackets. It is advised to book hotel in advance before going, so that tourists have ample time for negotiation. However, without prior bookings, finding accommodation won&#39;t still be an issue.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - Jaipur airport is the nearest at a distance of 184 kms. Taxies, cabs and state tourism buses can be boarded from here to cover the rest of the distance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Jhunjhunu is well connected by road to Delhi, Jaipur, Jodhpur, Bikaner and other major cities of the Shekhawati region.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train </strong>- The Jhunjhunu railway station is crossed by a couple of selected trains and the station is more connected to Delhi, Jaipur and Bikaner.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Rickshaws, taxies and buses are available for commuting within the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - JHUNJHUNU - (FAMOUS FOR GHEVAR IS A SWEET CAKE MADE WITH FLOUR AND SOAKED IN SUGAR SYRUP)</p>\r\n', ''),
(498, 14, 31, 752, 'Rajasthan', 'INDIA', 'KOTA', 'rajasthan-1845782_640.jpg', 'rajasthan-1845782_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kota is an attractive tourist destination on the banks of the Chambal river and is one of the most lively and charming cities in the state of Rajasthan. As per historians, the city was founded in the 12th century and Kota is a part of the Malwa Plateau. The basic establishment of Kota city was laid on 1264 AD as soon as the Rajput took over the place from a local tribal leader. With a glorious past and prosperous heritage and history, Kota kings were well known for their legendary performances in wars fought with Mughal rulers. A monument to Rajput traditions and bravery, Kota is famous for its wonderful heritage. Kota&rsquo;s coat of arms was extremely well known for its wonderful design and is exhibited in museums in Kota. Striking temples with numerous renowned stories behind them, historical forts and impressive palaces with Rajput architectural styles are all housed in the landscape of Kota. Kota is well-known for textile weaving, imposing handicrafts, oilseed and cotton milling, distilleries and dairy products. The renowned Doria Saris are created from the weaving mills of Kota. Metal handicrafts are specialty products of Kota&rsquo;s expert artists. Kota is also famous for the Victorian style structures built here modelled on British design. It is one of the most dynamic and picturesque cities in the state of Rajasthan, and an inviting tourist destination on the banks of Chambal river. India&#39;s oldest mountain range in the backdrop, views of spectacular sand dunes, a tiger trail, or bird watching in the town&#39;s wetlands are Kota&#39;s special offerings. Kota is known for abundance in flora and fauna as well as heritage. Its culture, safaris, sand dunes, heritage, lush forests and wildlife makes Kota destination unparallel. The fort overlooking the river Chambal is the foremost tourist attraction. It also houses a museum with a rich collection of art and artefacts and some elaborately painted chambers.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">To have a comfortable stay Kota offers an array of hotels in the city located at the different corner. The luxurious hotels offer a royal stay in the city. Standard rooms, deluxe room, and presidential suite with ballroom, courtyard, restaurant, lobby, and other rooms for various recreational activities are well constructed in the hotels to offers all basic to luxurious amenities in the town. The food includes all Indian and continental dishes with special cuisines form Rajasthani flavour. The room rents ranges from Rs. 300 to more than Rs. 6000 as per the hotel and facilities include.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Sanganer Airport, located at Jaipur, is the closest airbase to Kota. It is located at a distance of around 245 kms from the destination and is well connected to major cities of India including New Delhi and Mumbai.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Kota is well connected to nearby major cities by regular state buses of Rajasthan Road Transport Corporation. Travellers can avail bus services for Kota from Jodhpur, Udaipur, Chittorgarh, Ajmer, Bikaner, and Jaipur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Rajasthan Road is well connected to Kota with all other cities in Rajasthan. The highway passes through the Kota district are National Highway 76 which is the part of east west corridor and National Highway 12 which is under root Jaipur to Jabalpur.<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>By Train</strong> - The Kota Railway station is a foremost railhead which connects the place visited to other components of the country by regular teaches. Visitors can charter cabs to come to the town centre from the station.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- One could choose from buses, auto rickshaws or cycle rickshaws to move about the city. Tempo, a shared three wheeler, with mostly a fixed route is also a popular and the cheapest choice to move around.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>KOTA - [FAMOUS FOR LAAPSI IS A SWEET DISH MADE OF BROKEN WHEAT AND GHEE ALONG WITH NUTS, RAISINS AND DRIED FRUITS ; &nbsp;DAL BATTI CHURMA]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(499, 14, 31, 752, 'Rajasthan', 'INDIA', 'NAGAUR', 'camel-1845780_640.jpg', 'camel-1845780_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Nagaur is a historic city located in the state of Rajasthan. It was founded by the Naga Kshatriyas. The city serves as the headquarters of the Nagaur District. It lies between the popular tourist destinations, Bikaner and Jodhpur. The history of this place can be traced back to the days of the great epic the Mahabharata. It is said that the kingdom of Ahichhatrapur covered some areas of the present Nagaur District. According to mythology, the great Arjuna conquered Ahichhatrapur and offered it to his mentor, Guru Dronacharya. This city is famous for the Nagaur Fort which is a sandy fortress. It was constructed in the 2nd century by the Nagavanshis. This fort houses beautiful palaces, fountains, temples and gardens. Apart from this fort, Tarkeen Dargah is also a popular tourist attraction of Nagaur. This Dargah holds immense religious importance for the followers of Islam. Tourists planning a holiday trip to Nagaur can also see the Jain Glass Temple which is located behind the Kamla Tower in the city. This is quite a unique structure, being entirely made of glass. The impressive glass works of the interiors add more charm to the overall view. Tourists can find huge figures of 24 Jain Tirthankaras. Besides, Saiji ka Tanka is also a renowned tourist hotspot to visit in Nagaur. These palaces are famous for their exceptional architectural and interior designs. While visiting Nagaur, travellers can also see the Cenotaph of Amar Singh Rathore, Bansiwala Temple, Nath Ji ki Chhatri, and Barli. The climate of Nagaur remains hot and dry around the year due to scanty rainfall. Summer, monsoon and winter are the primary seasons here. Tourists are advised to plan a holiday trip to Nagaur between the months of October and November since this is the time when the weather remains relatively mild.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Accommodation available at Nagaur includes deluxe hotels and Economy hotels. &nbsp;Tourists can choose the accommodation as per their needs and budget.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The Jodhpur Airport is the nearest domestic airbase of Nagaur, at a distance of 140 kms. This airport is connected to major Indian destinations like Mumbai, Delhi, and Jaipur by frequent flights.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - Nagaur has its own railway station which is connected to major Indian tourist destinations like Jaipur, Jodhpur, Bikaner and Delhi by frequent trains.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road </strong>- Tourists planning a holiday trip to Nagaur can reach the destination by buses from Ajmer, Bikaner, Jodhpur and Jaipur. The capital city of Delhi is also well connected to the destination by regular bus services.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - JAIGOPAL CHHAGANLAL, LOCATED AT JLN HOSPITAL ROAD, NEW COLONY, AMAR SINGH COLONY - {FAMOUS FOR KULFI (FROZEN DESERT MADE FROM MILK, SUGAR AND CARDAMOM) AND MALPUA (IS A DESERT MADE FROM PLAIN FLOUR, RICE FLOUR, SUGAR AND COCONUT)}&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - BHOLA SETH RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT BHANDARIYON KI GALI - {FAMOUS FOR RABDI (SWEET MADE FROM MILK AND SUGAR)}<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - CHETAN PARKASH NAMKIN BHANDAR, LOCATED AT PUNIT NAGAR, SAINIK BASTI - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORI AND SAMOSA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - KANJI SWEETS AND CHAT BHANDAR, LOCATED AT PHED COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR PANI PURI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n5 - ARORA NAMKEEN, LOCATED AT KHATRI PURA - (FAMOUS FOR MIRCHI BADA AND KACHORI )</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(500, 14, 31, 752, 'Rajasthan', 'INDIA', 'PALI', 'india-1463868_640.jpg', 'india-1463868_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Pali, which is also known as the industrial city, is located in the state of Rajasthan. It is the administrative headquarters of the Pali district. This famous tourist hotspot lies on the banks of the River Bandi. Earlier, this place was known as Pallika and Palli. The place got its name from the Paliwal Brahmins who used to reside in the place during the ancient times. This place is famous for having a large number of textile industries and has been a trading centre since the historic times. The city is exceptionally known for its textile industries. It is a central point in exporting cotton and synthetic clothes to other states of India at a very low rate. One of the biggest cotton mills of Rajasthan is based in Pali. The city is well known for its holy temples and other marvellous places of sightseeing. Pali is considered an important historical town in the state and has seen the rise and fall of many dynasties which have ruled it over the ages. The town derives its name from the Paliwal Brahmins who used to reside here long time ago. There are quite a few temples and forts in the town. The Ranakpur Jain temple built in the 15th century by Rana Kumbha of Mewar, is one of the well known temples here. The Lakhotia Garden is another popular tourist site in Pali. It is located right in the centre of the town and is surrounded by a pond with a Shiva Temple in the middle of the garden. Pali is also known for its many Baoris which are step wells with intricate and artistic designs in each step. Being in the desert state of Rajasthan, the climate here is dry and extreme. Summer is quite hot and uncomfortable, while winter is pleasant making it the ideal time to visit the town.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">As Pali is a famous tourist location in Rajasthan, tourists can see many hotels and resorts in and around the city. The hotels charges differently for the rooms according to the facilities and services they offer. From the star hotels that have luxurious facilities to the budget hotels that are affordable to all types of people are available in Pali.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The Jodhpur Airport is the nearest household airbase to Pali. This airport is located at an expanse of 80 kms from the destination. It is attached to The Indira Gandhi International aerodrome of Delhi by frequent air travel. Furthermore, the Jodhpur aerodrome is well attached to foremost Indian destinations like Udaipur, Jaipur and Mumbai.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Pali has its own train&rsquo;s station which is connected to Guwahati, Bikaner, Jodhpur, Jaipur, Ajmer, etc. by frequent trains.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - The town is attached with all foremost towns of Rajasthan therefore you can effortlessly come to the town by road.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- Pali is linked through Rajasthan State Road Transport Corporation (RSRTC) and some private travel services. Pali is well attached by state run Buses coaches to locations such as Ajmer, Jodhpur and few other towns in the state. Tickets are bargain and buses are a good option.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - GULAB, LOCATED AT S-1, METRO PLAZA,, AMBEDKAR CIRCLE - (FAMOUS FOR HALWA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - VAISHNAV, LOCATED AT BHAWANI COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR PANI PURI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - BAJRANG, LOCATED AT NADI MOHALLA - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;DAL BAATI AND CHUTNEY WITH ONION)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - MERATIYA SWEET HOME, LOCATED AT NADI MOHALLA - (FAMOUS FOR MIRCH VADA AND KACHORI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n5 - ASHOK RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT SARRAFA BAZAR, NADI MOHALLA - {FAMOUS FOR LASSI AND RABADI (SWEET MADE FROM MILK AND SUGAR)}</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(501, 14, 31, 752, 'Rajasthan', 'INDIA', 'PRATAPGARH', 'lake-194841_640.jpg', 'lake-194841_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Pratapgarh is situated in the south eastern part of Rajasthan in Chittorgarh district. The area adjoins Udaipur, Banswara and Chittorgarh districts of Rajasthan and Ratlam, Mandsaur and Neemuch districts of Madhya Pradesh. It is situated at the junction of the Aravali mountain ranges and the Malwa Plateau; hence the characteristics of both prominently feature in the area. Pratapgarh is located at an average elevation of 491 mts. Pratapgarh district is newly constituted district in Rajasthan State. It came into existence on January 26th 2008 as 33rd district of Rajasthan. It was carved out from Chittorgarh district, Udaipur district and Banswara district. Famous for its Thewa art, the town is surrounded by tribal villages. It is second highest place in Rajasthan after Mount Abu. The city is a blend of old and new cultures. In nearby villages, the tribal culture still thrives. Every Sunday when the tribes come to the city to buy merchandise in the weekly haat market, the city also looks tribal. After the declaration as a district, new development plan has been executed in the city by state govt. Places to visit are Deogarh Fort, Bhagwan Shiva Place at Gotemshwar, Sita Mata Wild Sanctuary etc. Pratapgarh is a city that adds interest among the tourists to explore more and more areas. The main place of Tourist attraction is Pratapgarh Fort which is a remarkable sight to watch as it is built on a rock, which gives an eye catching look to the fort. It is closely related to the historical stories. Jakham Reservoir erected on Jakham River also attracts the tourists. Sitamata sanctuary, having mythology story of Goddess Sita is widely known for its flora and fauna. Historical temples of Pratpagarh like Devgarh known as devliya are surrounded with many more temples and small lakes.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Several budget hotels with a good, clean, homely environment can be found in Pratapgarh. But be sure to confirm availability before reaching.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest airport to Pratapgarh is Sanganer Airport, Jaipur which is 61 kms away from Pratapgarh city centre.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - The nearest railway station to Pratapgarh is Dausa Railway Station which is 43 kms away from Pratapgarh city centre.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Pratapgarh is well connected by road with major cities in Rajasthan, Madhya Pradesh and Gujrat. Regular government and private buses are available.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - PRATAPAGARH - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;SUKDI IS A SWEET DISH MADE FROM WHEAT FLOUR AND JAGGERY)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(502, 14, 31, 752, 'Rajasthan', 'INDIA', 'RAJSAMAND', 'kumbhal-garh-rajasthan-777800_640.jpg', 'kumbhal-garh-rajasthan-777800_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Rajsamand is a district of Indian state Rajasthan; it was carved out from the erstwhile district of Udaipur established on 10th April, 1991, and named after the famous artificial lake Rajsamand built by Maharana Raj Singh. Rajsamand the most rich district regarding history, religion, culture and mining includes Kumbhalgarh the birth place of Maharana Pratap, Haldighati the famous battle field the Thermopile, Dewair the Marathon of Mewar with Shrinathji the chief deity of Vaishnav religion besides Dwarikadheesh, Charbhuja and many Shiv temples. Rajsamand is very well known for its marble production as the largest producing district as well as the largest single unit in the whole country. Small scale industries in this district include mainly cottage and artisan units based on handloom, forest, leather, teracotta and livestock. Rajsamand is located at a distance of 15 kms from Nathdwara. This town lies on the banks of the Rajsamand Lake. It is famous for beautiful marble and handloom products. Kankroli Dam, Kumbhalgarh Fort and Haldighati are some of the notable tourist attractions of this place.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Accommodation facilities are not comparable to the very best in the country, though there are quite some hotels with decent basic facilities. One can easily find a room here at a good deal. Some of the most sought after hotels are Sardargarh Heritage Hotel and Devi Garh.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The airport situated in the closest proximity to Rajsamand is the Udaipur airport, which is 67 kms away from this beautiful town. Cabs and buses ply from the airport to take tourists to Rajsamand.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Rajsamand is well connected to other cities by the means of roads. There are direct buses from Jaipur, Jodhpur, Udaipur, Kota, Bhilwara, Ajmer, Beawer, Ahmedabad, Indore and New Delhi. One can also access this town in other vehicles comfortably.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Rajsamand does not have a railway station of its own. The nearest major railway station is Udaipur which is 59 kms away. All the major trains halt at Udaipur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Auto Rickshaws do not ply on meters here. One also has the option of roaming around the city in the buses.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - JALSA RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT 1 FLOOR PARAS GUEST HOUSE, MAHADEV COLONY, KANKROLI - (FAMOUS FOR CHOCOLATE &nbsp;SHAKE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - FOOD COUNTER, LOCATED AT MAHADEV COLONY, KANKROLI - (FAMOUS FOR SABJI PURI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - DWARKESH FAST FOOD, LOCATED AT NATHDWARA ROAD, IN FRONT OF VIJYA BANK, 100 FEET ROAD, KANKROL - (FAMOUS FOR CHEESE SANDWICH)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - SPECIAL BOMBAY, LOCATED AT NEAR RAJSAMAND LAKE, RAJNAGAR - KANKROLI ROAD, KANKROLI - (FAMOUS FOR BHEL PURI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - DUNGA BAA, LOCATED AT NATHDWARA RD, MAHADEV COLONY, KANKROLI - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - KKR RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT NEAR CLUB MAHINDRA, KUMBHALGARH, BEER KI BHAGAL - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;DAL-BATI-CHURMA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - DHUNII RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT TAHSIL ROAD, KANKROLI, NATHDWARA - (FAMOUS FOR CORN CHILLY)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(503, 14, 31, 752, 'Rajasthan', 'INDIA', 'SAWAI MADHOPUR', 'rajasthan-1473474_1280.jpg', 'rajasthan-1473474_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Sawai Madhopur lies on the eastern edge of Rajasthan state and is a district headquarters. &nbsp;The city covers an area of 5043 sq kms. It is bounded by Dausa district on the north, Karauli district on the northwest and west, the Chambal River, and across it Madhya Pradesh state and Kota district, on the southwest side, Bundi district to the southeast side and Tonk district to the east. Gangapur, Ranthambhore and Sawai Madhopur are the cities in Sawai Madhopur district. The town is named after Sawai Madho Singh I, the Maharaja of Jaipur, who built the town during the late 18th century. Sawai Madhopur is a secluded small town in the state of Rajasthan and cannot be termed as a fully developed city. Despite this, Sawai Madhopur experiences a huge footfall of tourists annually. The world famous Ranthambhore National Park with the largest population of tigers in the state takes the credit for this density of tourists here. Sawai Madhopur is a place worth visiting for other than the Ranthambhore National Park. It entices the tourists with wide ranging views of mounts, grasslands, beautiful pastures and majestic ranges of Aravalli and Vindhya mountains surrounding the city. Apart from the scenic nature the town also has some wonderful temples that have a lot of religious and historic importance. Paddy, maize, pulses, jowar, bajra, sesamum, groundnut, sugarcane, red chillies, wheat, and barley are the main crops of this district.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Sawai Madhopur has many accommodation options catering to the needs of the tourists arriving in the city. There are two luxury hotels that have established beautiful accommodation facilities just next to the Ranthambhore national park itself. Apart from a few luxury hotels many other budget and economy hotels are available meeting the needs of tourists. All these hotels in Sawai Madhopur provide modern amenities and a comfortable stay to their guests.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Sawai Madhopur does not have an airport. The nearest airport is Jaipur, at a distance of 112 kms. Jaipur is well connected by air to many other Indian cities</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Sawai Madhopur is a railway junction and is on the Delhi Mumbai main railway line. Hence it is connected to all the major cities of India via railways.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Sawai Madhopur is connected by a good network of roads with the other cities of Rajasthan as well as with Agra and Delhi. Sawai Madhopur is partly connected to State Highway 1 and National Highway 11.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Metered taxis, cabs and RSRTC buses connect this city with other Rajasthan cities and also Agra and Delhi. Apart from the RSRTC buses and private tour operator&rsquo;s buses ply from Sawai Madhopur to other parts of Rajasthan and the close by attractions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Tourists in Sawai Madhopur have multiple options when it comes to wandering around the city, hopping from one spot to another. While buses, tempos and auto rickshaws are the primary mode of transport within the city, jeeps and gypsies are available en route to landmark places like the Ranthambore National Park and the Ranthambore Fort.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - KANHA, LOCATED AT INDRA COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR CHILLY POTATO, PANEER TIKKA, PAV BHAJI AND PANI PURI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - ZAIKA THE TASTE, LOCATED AT CIVIL LINES, INDRA COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;DESI GHEE ALOO SABJI AND LASSI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - SHRI JANATA JODHPUR, LOCATED AT RAILWAY COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR MASALA DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - MANISHA RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT RANTHAMBHORE ROAD, NEAR CITY HEART HOTEL - (FAMOUS FOR DAAL FRY AND SOME BUTTER CHAPATTI)</strong></p>\r\n', '');
