(504, 14, 31, 752, 'Rajasthan', 'INDIA', 'SIKAR', 'monument-162779_1280.jpg', 'monument-162779_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Sikar is a popular tourist destination located in the north eastern part of the Indian state, Rajasthan. It is the second most developed city after the Pink City, Jaipur and serves as the administrative headquarters of the Sikar district. This place shares its boundaries with Jhunjhunu district, Churu district, Nagaur district, and Jaipur district of the state. This city was historically known as Beer Bhan Ka Bass and was the capital of the state, Thikana Sikar ruled by the Shekhawati kings. One of the most important districts in the Shekhawati, Sikar is safely located in the shade of huge walls with seven entrance gates to the town. Sikar is a good getaway for lazing around, drinking in a new culture, doing photo walks and talking to the locals while gawking at marvellous monuments. The forts, palaces and havelis with the exotic craft of fresco and intricate architecture do not fail to amaze. Living amidst such great work of art, the locals understand art and are passionate about it. Sikar, combined with other tourist attractions in the Shekhawati region could be a great trip to royal palaces with many unheard stories, forts and the many wars they have been a witness to, frescoes and the beauty of art and culture and the royal yet humble hospitality of the royal state.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are a variety of hotels from different budget brackets and facilities to choose from. With tariff starting from 300/day going up to 3000/day, it is suggested that while booking the hotel, one must first compare the services provided, location and tariff etc. before finalizing the hotel.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Jaipur Airport is 116 kms from Sikar. Taxies, state and private buses from Jaipur are available to Sikar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - The National Highway NH 11 connects Sikar to Jaipur, Bikaner and other parts of the country. This highway is going to be a four lane highway, ensuring good road connectivity to the region.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Buses coaches are furthermore accessible to Sikar from towns like Delhi, Jaipur, Jodhpur, and Bikaner.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Sikar railway station is connected with other cities in the Shekhawati region and to the key cities of the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Shared jeeps and buses can be used for travelling within the city. For covering places away from Sikar, it is suggested to book a taxi and cover various spots in the itinerary on a day.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - JAWAHAR JI PANDYA KI DUKKAN, INSIDE NANI GATE, STATION ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;KACHORI,SAMOSA AND DAHI VADA)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">2 - JEETU MAWA BHANDAR, AT GINDAR CHOWK, DOLIYON KA BASS, BAJAJ ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR RASGULLA AND CHAM CHAM)<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(505, 14, 31, 752, 'Rajasthan', 'INDIA', 'SIROHI', 'W3.jpg', 'W4.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Sirohi is surrounded and influenced by three traditional cultures, Marwar, Mewar and Gujarat. So, its festivals and fairs are colourful. Sirohi is a nice district situated at the south western part of Rajasthan. The district is bounded by Pali district in the northeast, by Udaipur district in the East, by Gujarat State and Jalore in the West. It is the third smallest district of Rajasthan. The district derives its name from Siranwa hills on the western slope of which it stands. Sirohi is one of the fascinating districts of Rajasthan offering some good places of tourist&#39;s importance like Mount Abu, Sun Temple, Chandravati, Ajari Temple, Sarvadham Temple, Bamanvadji Temple, and Pavapuri Temple etc. In Sirohi district Mount Abu is as diverse as the city itself. It was once a part of the Chauhan kingdom of Rajasthan and served as a summer resort for the Rajput kings of the region. It is famous for Temples, that&rsquo;s why it is popularly also known as Devnagri. Sirohi, earlier known as Shivpuri was founded by Rao Sobhaji. Peoples come to visit Vasant Garh also known as Vata because of number of banyan trees over there; it was founded by Rishi Vasistha. Ajari Temple dedicated to lord Shiva, known for bulky honeycombs, Bamanvad Ji Temple dedicated to Mahavir Bhagwan, Karodidhwaj Temple known to be built by followers of the Sun is in the Shape of a Horse is popularly known. The other key attraction of tourists is the oldest marble temple of the Rajasthan Mirpur Temple and Mandakini Kund located opposite of the Sharneshwar ji Temple built with lime and bricks having giant statues of elephants at the entrance.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">As there are several historical monuments and temples in and around the city, many people from various corners of the country visit here. Tourists will easily get good accommodation in the city, as the city has many luxury hotels that provide all amenities and services to the guests in the beautifully adorned luxury rooms. Hotels in Sirohi city provide a broad range of facilities and services to the people during their holiday trip in Rajasthan.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- The easiest way to reach Sirohi by air is to travel to Jodhpur Airport, which is 187 kms away and Udaipur Airport, which is 240 kms away from the city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Sirohi district has nine railway stations and among which the main station is located in the city. It is named Sirohi road railway station. It is connected to many main stations of major cities of India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - The Rajasthan state buses connect Sirohi to other nearby cities of the state. There are also many private bus services to Sirohi from nearby cities. Different types of buses like AC, Non AC, Sleeper, Semi sleeper etc will be available at various fares.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - VAJOBA, LOCATED AT GOYALI CHAURAHA, TEEN BATTI CIR, AIRSTRI - (FAMOUS FOR VADA PAV)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - PANDU MANCHURIAN CENTER, LOCATED AT PALACE ROAD, NEAR AHINSA CIRCLE, VEDHAYNATH COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR MANCHURIAN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - MAHALAXMI BHOJNALAYA, LOCATED IN SIROHI - (FAMOUS FOR PANEER BHURJI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - SANTOSH VADAPAV CENTRE SIYANA, LOCATED AT SIANA- SIROHI MAIN ROAD, RAJENDER NAGAR COLONY, BUS STATION - (FAMOUS FOR VADA PAV)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - RABDI KING SANWAL BHAI, LOCATED AT RAILWAY STATION ROAD, FALNA, ABU ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR RABDI IS A SWEET MADE FROM MILK AND SUGAR)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(506, 14, 31, 752, 'Rajasthan', 'INDIA', 'TONK', 'india-1463863_640.jpg', 'india-1463863_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Tonk is a town, situated on the banks of the River Banas in the Tonk district of Rajasthan. Once a princely state, the town was ruled by various dynasties until the time of Indian independence. It is located at a distance of 95 kms from the city of Jaipur. The town of Tonk describes an anecdote of the bygone era through several historical monuments present in the area. There are several tourist attractions in and around the town. Sunehri Kothi or the Mansion of Gold is the most visited tourist attraction in the area. Constructed by Nawab Mohammed Ibrahim Ali Khan for music, dance and poetry recitals, the building also showcases some fantastic glass paintings. It is located near Bada Kuwa on Najar Bagh Road and is also called the Sheesh Mahal. Walls of the building are polished in gold, and the halls present a pretty picture with enamelled mirrors. Apart from Sunehri Kothi, there are several other historical monuments which exhibit the rich history of the town. Rasiya Ke Tekri is one such tourist attraction which has an interesting fable behind its name. The Jama Masjid of Tonk is one of the biggest mosques in India and several devotees travel to the town to visit this Islamic shrine. Designed in accordance with Mysore Gardens and Hiran Magari Park, Shivaji Garden is an excellent tourist destination. Tourists can also visit Hathi Bhata to witness the exceptional creativity of the artist, who carved a single stone into an elephant. The best time to visit this town is between the months of October and February when the weather is cool and pleasant. Tourists can also visit this historically rich town during the monsoon season, which is characterised by moderate temperature and slight rainfall.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Tonk has a number of hotels spread out at different regions. Tourist can find all the hotels and other accommodations at specific locations. Hotels here lay complete focus on cleanliness, hygiene and ambience, quality of services, safety and comfort of guests.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport to Tonk is Jaipur, which is 100 kms away from the town. The Jaipur Airport is the closest airbase and is well connected by flights to several locations across the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The nearest railway station to Tonk is Banasthali Newai, at a distance of 35 kms from the town. Jaipur is the next nearest railway station, 100 kms from Tonk and is connected to the rest of the country by frequent trains.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Rajasthan State Road Transport Corporation (RSRTC) operates several buses to Tonk from places like Delhi, Jaipur, Ajmer, Kota, Bundi, etc. Private buses and taxis are also available from various nearby places to Tonk.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Tonk is located along National Highway 12 and it is connected to places such as Jaipur and Jablapur by road.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - KACHORI CENTRE, LOCATED AT SHASTRI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - KHANDELWAL DHABA, LOCATED AT 115, TONK ROAD, SANGANER, KUNDAN NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR BUTTER PANNER MASALA,MALAI KOFTA AND DAL TADKA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - BITS AND BITES CAFE, LOCATED AT CHAWANI ROAD, KALI PALTAN - (FAMOUS FOR BURGER, PIZZA AND CHOCHO SHAKE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - SHREE BALAJI CAFE, LOCATED AT DISTRICT SHOPPING CENTRE, NEAR LAXMI MANDIR CINEMA, SAHAKAR MARG, LAXMI COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR SOUTH INDIAN FOOD)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n5 - SCORPIAN A PUB CITY, LOCATED AT SUNNY PARADISE 6TH FLOOR , TONK ROAD NEAR KAMAL AND COMPANY, NEW LIGHT COLONY, BAJAJ NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR PANEER TIKKA &nbsp;AND CHILLI POTATO)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - J.M.D BAKERS AND FAST FOOD, LOCATED AT OPPOSITE BMW SHOWROOM NEAR IDEA OFFICE, MAIN, TONK ROAD, KAILASH PURI COLONY, DURGAPURA - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA, SANDWICHES AND PUFF PASTRY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - JODHPUR MISTHAN BHANDAR, LOCATED AT INDIRA COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORI AND SWEETS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n8 - SODHANI SWEETS PVT LTD, LOCATED AT OPPOSITE TONK ROAD, NAGAR NIGAM, LALKOTHI - (FAMOUS FOR PYAAJ KACHORI, SAMOSA AND MIRCHI BADA AND LASSI)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(507, 14, 31, 1654, '', 'INDIA', 'CUDDALORE', 'dhanushkodi-1765163_640.jpg', 'dhanushkodi-1765163_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Cuddalore, situated on the coast of Bay of Bengal is one of the fastest growing cities in the state of Tamil Nadu. The name Cuddalore refers to Sea town in Tamil language and the town is indeed abundant with beautiful beaches. The city is also famous for its magnificent temples. Cuddalore has two districts namely the Old Town and the New town. The Gedilam River separates the Old town from Thirupadiripuliyur, the New town, while flowing through the town. The old town was called Islamabad during the Mughal rule, and it continues to be a Muslim dominated area. Cuddalore was also the capital of the English Possessions in the period from 1748 to 1752. Located in the state of Tamil Nadu, Cuddalore is a beautiful city to visit. Being situated along the Bay of Bengal, Cuddalore is well known for its eye catching beaches, one of them being the Silver Beach which is the second longest beach in Tamil Nadu. Cuddalore travel guide is full of references to the mesmerizing sceneries and serene spots. The city is an awesome destination to spend holidays and leisure time as it is dotted with friendly ambience and coveted tranquillity. The Cuddalore town is famous for its various Shiva and Vaishnava temples. Some of the most famous temples are Pataleeshwarar temple, Tiruvaheendirapuram temple, Mangalapureeswarar temple, Sudarkozhunthuteesar temple, to name a few. The city has also become a major tourist destination thanks to its numerous beaches.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">For the convenience of tourists, various accommodations such as hotels and lodges are developed in the town. The hotels have luxurious rooms with all modern amenities, available at reasonable prices. They offer services like laundry, wifi, bars and multicuisine restaurants. Some of the hotels also make arrangements for sightseeing.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- The closest airport to Cuddalore is the Pondicherry Airport which is about 25 kms from Cuddalore. However, Chennai Airport is the major airport near Cuddalore. It is located at a distance of about 180 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The city has two railway Stations, the Thirupadirippuliyur station and the Cuddalore Port Junction. Trains are available to most towns and cities in Tamil Nadu and also other towns of South India from these stations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Cuddalore city is located on NH 45A giving it easy access via road. Buses are available from nearby cities such as Chennai, Salem, Trichy, Coimbatore and Thiruvannamalai. There are also a few buses from Bangalore.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - CUDDALORE - [FAMOUS FOR KADALA KOZHAMBU(PEANUT CURRY) IS A VEGETARIAN DISH MADE FROM PEANUTS(VER KADALAI),EGG PLANT/BRINJAL(KATHIRKAAI),TAMARIND(PULI),METHI AND MUSTARD(KADUGU)SEEDS(VENDAHAYAM),CHANNA DAL(KADALAI PARUPPU),RED CHILLI (VARA MILAGAI) AND CURRY LEAVES(KARUVAPILLAI) ; MEEN KUZHABU (FISH CURRY) IS A NON VEGETARIAN DISH MADE FROM FISH]&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(508, 14, 31, 1654, '', 'INDIA', 'DINDIGUL', 'hill-801958_640.jpg', 'hill-801958_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Dindigul is a city located in the state of Tamil Nadu. Dindigul derives its name from the words Thindu which means pillow and kal which means rock. It refers to the bare hills which overlook the city. The city is located between the Palani Hills and the Sirumalai Hills and is a bed of fertile land apt for agriculture. Dindigul is surrounded by many districts and cities. On its north are Kari and Erode districts, on its south lies Madurai and on its west lies Tiruppur and Kerala. The city of Dindigul is popular by various other names such as Biryani City, City of Locks and Textile and Tannery. Apart from the majestic fort, there are also a few temples and holy rivers that can be visited in Dindigul. N Panjampatti which is located at a distance of 7km away from Dindigul is also a must visit. There is also a 300 year old Roman Catholic Church which is worth a visit. Moreover, the Christ the King Church and the St. Joseph Church are other important churches of the city. Close to Dindigul is Sirumalai Hill resort which is a pleasant hill station located on the way to Dindigul Nathan. Another attraction is the meeting point of the rivers Vaigai, Maruda and Manjalaru which has become a popular pilgrimage site close to the city. Trekkers can take a short trek to the small hill of Mala Kottai which is located in the city. The most famous historical landmark of Dindigul is the Rock Fort which is located atop a hill. The summers in Dindigul are hot and humid as the city experiences a tropical climate. The best time of the year to visit Dindigul is therefore during the monsoons and the winters when the weather is mild and pleasant.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Dindigul is a major trade centre of Tamil Nadu state and hence, a lot of merchants, businessman and tourists visit this place to explore the trade and other famous parts in the city. The hotels in Dindigul are pretty economical in this city and one can afford these with all modern facilities at reasonable prices. There are various packages which are provided by many hotels to make your stay in this city more delightful.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- The closest airport to Dindigul is Madurai airport which is located at a distance of 84 kms from the city. One can take a taxi or bus from Madurai to Dindigul. Madurai airport is connected to Chennai airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Dindigul railway station is connected to all important stations of Tamil Nadu such as Chennai, Coimbatore and Madurai. Trains to the city are frequent, and the easiest, most comfortable and least expensive option to reach the city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Dindigul lies by two main National Highways namely NH 7 and NH 209. Regular bus services are available from Dindigul to all important towns and cities of Tamil Nadu.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Local transport is by means of bus, taxi or auto rickshaw. Also, being a hill station, the best way to enjoy its ambience is by travelling on foot.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - MUTTON BIRIYANI, LOCATED AT SALAI RD, SPENCER COMPOUND - (FAMOUS FOR PONRAM MULTICUISINE RESTAURANT)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - PONRAM FOOD SQUARE, LOCATED AT THADICOMBU ROAD, CHENNAMANAYAKKANPATTI, SETTINAICKENPATTI - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN PARATHA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - SHREE SARAVANABHAVAN, LOCATED AT THIRUVALLUVAR SALAI, SPENCER COMPOUND - (FAMOUS FOR APPAM IS A TYPE OF PANCAKE MADE FROM RICE BATTER AND PANNIYARAM IS A DISH MADE FROM RICE AND BLACK LENTILS BATTER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - JJ RECIPE CORNER, LOCATED AT A.K.COMPLEX, AARTHY THEATRE ROAD, V O C NAGAR, ANNA NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR FRIED RICE EGG CURRY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - JAI ANJANEYA RESTAURANT, LOCATED IN DINDIGUL - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;IDLI AND VADA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n6 - KRISHNAYAR MITTAI KADAI, LOCATED AT NAGAL NAGAR - {FAMOUS FOR JALEBI (SWEET)}</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(509, 14, 31, 1654, '', 'INDIA', 'ERODE', 'summer-1974258_640.jpg', 'summer-1974258_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Erode city is the headquarters of the Erode district in Tamil Nadu. The city is located at the heart of South Indian Peninsula, approximately 400 kms southwest of Chennai and almost 100 kms west of the commercial city Coimbatore, on the banks of Bhavani and Cauvery rivers. Erode is famous for power loom textile products, handloom products and readymade clothes. Therefore, it is also known as Tex valley of India or Loom city of India. Bed sheets, lungies, towels, cotton saris, dhotis, carpets and printed fabrics are sold here wholesale, and in the festive season, the fabric dealers make a lot of income. These products are also exported to other parts of the globe. The city is also popular for the cultivation of turmeric. In 850 AD, the Erode city was under the rule of the Chera emperors. This city came under the regime of Cholas Between 1000 AD to 1275 AD later in 1276 AD it was under the authority of the Pandias. It was during this period that the Kalingarayan Channel was dug under the supervision of the emperor Veerapandian. Then came the reign of Muslims and thereafter the Madurai kings governed. After that Tippu Sultan and Hyder Ali ruled the city, and in the year 1799, East India Company captured the government. Normally, the Erode district has a dry climate and the rain is unsatisfactory. In the months of February and March, the climate of the place is very humid in general, especially alongside the Cauvery River. In April, the climate becomes hotter and attains maximum humidity. In the months of June, July and August chill wind flows all the way through Palghat gap, but as it arrives at the region under Erode, the cooling effect goes down and the weather gets warm and dusty.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are different categories of hotels in Erode, suited for every person in Erode. One can choose the hotel according to the budget. However, all hotels in Erode have the best facilities within its range. The West Inn Hotel, Hotel Oasis Grand, Hotel Sivaranjani, Hotel LE Jardin are some of the important hotels in the city of Erode.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><br />\r\n<strong>By Air</strong> - Coimbatore International Airport serves as the nearest airport to Erode. Travellers can board a flight till Coimbatore and then travel rest of the distance to Erode by road.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>By Bus</strong> - State buses of Tamil Nadu as well as many private buses serve the city of Erode. Travellers can board buses from nearby places like Salem, Coimbatore to reach erode by road.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>By Train </strong>- Erode Junction railway station connects the city to several other cities such as New Delhi, Chennai, Puri, Mysore, Patna etc. It is located at a distance of around 1.8 km from the main town of Erode.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - The National Highway 47 connecting the districts Salem, Coimbatore and Kanyakumari, passes through three important points of Erode district, Perundurai, Bhavani and Chithode.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - ERODE - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;KILLU KARI IS A SPICY MUTTON GRAVY ; UTTAPPAM IS A SNACK MADE FROM RICE FLOUR, WHITE LENTILS ; PORICHA KOOTU ; PAYASAM IS A DESERT DISH MADE FROM MILK GHEE AND SUGAR ; PALLIPALAYAM CHICKEN IS A NON VEGETARIAN DISH ; KATTI PARUPPU IS A DAL CURRY] &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(510, 14, 31, 1654, 'Tamil Nadu', 'INDIA', 'HOSUR', 'sunset-72866_1280.jpg', 'sunset-72866_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Hosur lies at a distance of 40 kms away from Bengaluru and it falls under the Krishnagiri district of Tamil Nadu. Although a busy industrial city, Hosur is famous for its pleasant weather and plentiful greenery all year long. It is sometimes referred as Little England due to its lovely climate. It is an important hub for automobile industry and this makes the city more popular. It gets its name from Kannada and it means new settlement. What is today a modern industrial city was once an important border city during the reign of Tipu Sultan. During the British rule, it was an important city lying on the borders of the British Raj and Tipu Sultan&rsquo;s Mysore. Hosur was originally founded by the Hoysala dynasty king Rama Natha in 1290 AD. Located in the state of Tamil Nadu and is a beautiful town of Krishnagiri district, Hosur is the civil headquarters of a Taluk in the district and is located at a distance of 40 kms south east of the Bangalore and 48 kms northwest of the district. It is extremely famous for its manufacturing industries and the amazing weather. The city is a chief industrial centre for various Manufacturing and Automobile industries. The great International market giants have established their subsidiaries in the town. It is said that the town is more than 800 years old. The rock paintings and carvings of the city imply that the region was under the control of the Palaeolithic, Neolithic and Mesolithic ages. The city was established during the year 1290 by King Rama Nathan and belonged to Hoysala Dynasty.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">If one is travelling through the town of Hosur and looking for some accommodation for rest then the town offers with great options of hotels where tourists can stay. These hotels provide all the modern amenities, services and delicious food.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The closest airport to Hosur is the Bangalore International Airport and the next best option is the airport at Chennai.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - There are various trains that ply directly from Hosur to various important towns and cities in Andhra Pradesh, Karnataka and Tamil Nadu. That&rsquo;s not all, from trains that ply between Bangalore and Chennai stop at Hosur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- This is the best way to reach Hosur. Its convenient location on the National Highway 7 makes Hosur easily accessible by road. There are umpteenth number of the buses, both government run and private, connecting Hosur to all the important nearby cities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - VASAVI CAFE, LOCATED AT TALUK OFFICE ROAD, HAMUMANTHAPURAM, ANNA NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR MASALA DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - GANI HOTEL, LOCATED AT 55/1, BANGALORE BY PASS ROAD, SRI NAGAR, HOSUR - (FAMOUS FOR BIRYANI AND GRILLED CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - &nbsp;ANJANEYA VILAS, LOCATED AT DENKINUKOTA ROAD, SHANTHI NAGAR WEST - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;SOUTH INDIAN FOOD)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - SANGEETH SAGAR, LOCATED AT KG SAMY COMPLEX, OPP TO LIBERTY SHOWROOM, BAGALUR ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;MANCHURIAN, VEGETABALE GRAVY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - BALLE BALLE &nbsp;RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT NANJUNDESWARA NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN FRY, MUTTON SHORBA, CHILLI POTATO AND GULAB JAMUN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - CHINNASWAMY NAIDU, LOCATED AT SIPCOT PH. I, HOSUR - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN BIRYANI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n7 - AGARWAL BHAVAN SWEETS, LOCATED AT NETHAJI ROAD, ANNA NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR MILK CAKE, KAJU BARFI AND SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>8 - SMALL FAST FOOD SHOP, LOCATED AT TANK STREET, ANNA NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR MUTTON SOUPS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(511, 14, 31, 1654, 'Tamil Nadu', 'INDIA', 'KANCHIPURAM', 'art-186962_640.jpg', 'art-186962_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kanchipuram is perhaps the oldest city of Tamil Nadu that has still managed to retain its old world charm. The city is famous for not only its temples but also for having been the Capital city of the Pallava Kings. Even today the city is sometimes called by its old names of Kanchiampathi and Conjeevaram. Foreign tourists know Kanchipuram as the The City of Thousand Temples. The city is easily accessible since it is located just 72 kms from Chennai, the capital of Tamil Nadu. Kanchipuram is a revered city for the Hindus since it is among one of the seven holiest places that every Hindu should visit during their lifetime. According to Hindu mythology, moksha or salvation can be attained by a visit to all of the seven holy places. The city is a sacred place for the devotees of Lord Shiva as well as Lord Vishnu. There are many temples dedicated to Shiva and Vishnu in the city of Kanchipuram. Among these temples the more popular ones are the Varadhraja Perumal Temple dedicated to God Vishnu and Ekambaranatha Temple which is one among the Panchabootha Sthalams or the five temples of Shiva representing the five elements. Legend has it that the city got its name because of the numerous Lord Vishnu temples that are built within the city premises. Ka stands for Lord Brahma who is believed to have anchi or worshipped Lord Vishnu in this city thus, giving the place the name of Kanchipuram. The weather in Kanchipuram oscillates between hot summers and pleasant winters.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The boarding houses and lodges are all decently constructed and adequately facilitated. Hotel Simla Lodge, Jaya Bala, GRT Regency are amongst the famous hotels and GRT Regency leaves a smile on your face by providing free Wireless Internet.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The closest airport to Kanchipuram is the Anna International Airport in Chennai. Kanchipuram is about 62 kms from the airport and it will take around 70 minutes to reach from Chennai airport to Kanchipuram.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Kanchipuram is well connected with the rest of the south Indian cities via a strong network of trains. Kanchipuram has one station, the Chengalpattu Railway Station that is on the Chengalpattu Arrakonam line.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Kanchipuram is well connected to Chennai by Bangalore NH 4 road. So, one can easily get in here by hired taxi or private vehicle.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - One can easily reach Kanchipuram by bus as State owned public transport system connects Kanchipuram to many cities and Chennai. Private buses are also available.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Three wheeler auto rickshaws are available. There are a number of taxis that hang out just north of the bus station, east of the roundabout. If travelling in a large group, it is advisable to negotiate a driver for a day instead of dealing with auto rickshaws.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - KANCHIPURAM - [FAMOUS FOR KUZHAMBU IS A CURRY MADE FROM VARIETY OF DALS AND VEGETABLES ; PAYASAM IS A SWEET DISH MADE BY BOILING RICE, BROKEN WHEAT, TAPIOCA OR VERMICELLI WITH MILK AND SUGAR ; RASAM IS A SOUP]&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(512, 14, 31, 1654, 'Tamil Nadu', 'INDIA', 'KARAIKUDI', 'ganesh-377490_640.jpg', 'ganesh-377490_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Karaikudi is a municipal town located in Sivagangai district of the state of Tamil Nadu. The place is the most famous in the entire municipality because it is also the largest town in the district. It is part of the Chettinad region that includes a total of 75 villages. The town is on the highway that connects Trichy and Rameshwaram. It is a well known town in this southern state of India mainly because of the style of houses that is unique to the place. The houses in this town are constructed using the limestone that is called karai veedu in local language. Some people also believe that the town got its name from the plant of Karai which is found in abundance in the place. Karaikudi was earlier counted in the Ramanathapuram district and achieved the status of a municipality in 1928. Unfortunately, not much is known about the history of Karaikudi and according to locals the place was established in the 18th century since the oldest known temple in the town dates back to 1800 AD. It is a well known fact that the family of Chettiars was instrumental in developing the town of Karaikudi. Even today, the Chettiar community makes the majority of the population of the town. They are into trade and commerce ever since the establishment of Karaikudi. They have helped shape the town and brought it into prominence by building educational institutes, funding banks, constructing temples and celebrating festivals in the traditional ways. They have also taken upon them the onus of bringing social reforms. To make Karaikudi self sufficient in every way, Vallal Alagappar, who belonged to the Chettiar family, established the Alagappa University in the place and this university has a good nationwide ranking. Many people from in and around the town of Karaikudi come to the place for engineering. The university is considered as having one of the best engineering colleges in the country.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Luxury hotels in Karaikkudi are designed to devour a unique experience. These hotels are adorned by domestic and international visitors. The hotels showcase the heritage and architecture of Karaikudi&#39;s native citizens. Chidambara Villas plays a very important role in the list of luxury hotels in Karaikudi. The hotel is used as a venue for business meetings and weddings. To meet up with this every increasing populace of tourists, there are many budget friendly hotels in Karaikudi. These hotels are made of basic amenities and facilities that would make the stay comfortable and easy.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport to Karaikudi is at Tiruchirapalli or Trichy. This is an International Airport and is about 90 kms from Karaikudi. The Madural Airport is also located 90 kms from Karaikudi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Karaikudi Junction is connected via the Trichy Rameshwaram railway line as well as by Mayiladuthurai Karaikudi railway line. There are about five trains that run daily on these two lines and will take tourists to Karaikudi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - There are many state owned as well as private buses that regularly connect Karaikudi with other towns. There are two bus terminals in the town; the Old Bus Stand in southern Karaikudi and the New Bus Stand in the northern part of Karaikudi.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - KARAIKUDI - (FAMOUS FOR CHETTINAD IS A TYPE OF MEAT DISH)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(513, 14, 31, 1654, 'Tamil Nadu', 'INDIA', 'KRISHNAGIRI', 'art-1283342_6401.jpg', 'art-1283342_6402.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Krishnagiri, the 30th district of Tamil Nadu, India, owes its name to the numerous black granite hillocks that are a part of the landscape. With a surface area of about 5143 sq kms Krishnagiri as a travel destination has a lot to offer. While the KRP dam is the most popular tourist attraction, Krishnagiri houses several other archaeological sites, temples, parks, forts and memorials amidst breathtaking nature. City of Mangoes, Krishnagiri, located in the state of Tamil Nadu is a small city and an extremely fertile region generally known for its agricultural practices. Nestled beautifully at the distance of 90 kms from Bangalore and 45 kms from Hosur, Krishnagiri is a popular tourist spot in Southern India. The city is widely known for its Krishnagiri Dam, which is one of the primary attractions of the place and draws a large number of tourists round the year. Due to the existence of numerous archaeological sites, Krishnagiri is believed to be one of the oldest colonized places in the country. Krishnagiri travel guide is full of references to the historical significance. Krishnagiri was ruled by the Kongu Nadu Kings and Chola Kings. Their influences can be seen even today here. Other dynasties that ruled the town were Pandas, Cholas, Nulambas, Cheras and Bijapur empires. The evidences during the Iron Age can be seen in the city. Cultivation of Mangoes, the national fruit of India is the major source of income of the people of the Tamil Nadu. The major crop of Krishnagiri district with 300 sq kms area of farming is Mango. The district produces around 300000 tons on an annual basis. A lot of mango varieties like Alphonso and Thothapuri are produced in this district. Krishnagiri also hosts an Annual Exhibition of Mangoes at New Delhi. Many delicious varieties of mangoes are exhibited during the festival.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Krishnagiri being an important tourist attraction Visitors can find them a comfortable accommodation in the Hotel Tamil Nadu operated by the Tamil Nadu Tourism Development Corporation (TTDC). Krishnagiri has some deluxe and many medium to budget hotel options with all facilities to make the stay a memorable one.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Bangalore international airport is the closest international airport to Krishnagiri. Bangalore being 92 kms away from Krishnagiri, Bangalore airport is also the closest airport to Krishnagiri.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The Southern Railway system of India is reasonably well connected and Krishnagiri is no exception. The closest railway station to Krishnagiri is Hosur railway station. Trains that connect Bangalore and Chennai travel through Hosur making it a well connected station.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Krishnagiri is well connected by road to most major cities and towns between Karnataka and Tamil Nadu. National Highways such as NH 7, NH 46, NH 66, NH 207 and NH 219 intersect at Krishnagiri.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - The new bus stand built on the outskirts of Krishnagiri is well connected by road to all the major cities in India. Buses can be taken from Bangalore, Chennai, Hyderabad, Pune, Vishakapatnam, and Nagpur. Both Government buses and private carriers run buses regularly from Krishnagiri.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - KRISHNAGIRI - FAMOUS FOR ADHIRASAM IS A SWEET MADE FROM RICE FLOUR AND JAGGERY ; FAMOUS FOR CHIPPI APPAM IS AN APPETIZER MADE WITH RICE FLOUR AND OYSTERS ; KUZHAMBU IS A DISH MADE FROM VARITIES OF DAL]</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(514, 14, 31, 1654, 'Tamil Nadu', 'INDIA', 'NAGAPATTINAM', 'beach-1204401_1280.jpg', 'beach-1204401_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Nagapattinam is a town located in the Nagapattinam district of Tamil Nadu. The town serves as the district headquarters. Located on the eastern coast of the Indian peninsula by the Bay of Bengal, the district emerged after being diverged from the Thanjavur district. The town is located at a distance of 270 kms from Chennai. The place gets its name from the two words Nagar which is used to refer to people belonging to Sri Lanka and Pattinam which means town. The town has been known by various other names in history. During the rule of the Cholas, the town was called Cholakula Vallipattinam. The place was referred to as Nikam by Ptolemy. The Portuguese referred to it as the city of Coromandel. Nagapattinam is famous for its rich history and culture. It is also famous for its harbours which are some of the best in the country. The town also attracts several pilgrims who come to offer their prayers in the temples located here. Besides the temples, the town also houses the ancient Nagore Dargha which was built in the 16th century. Nagapattinam is also located very close to Velankanni which is famous for the Basilica of Our Lady of Good Health Church. There is also a salt swamp located near Nagapattinam town which is well known for its bio diversity. Kodikkarai is a famous wildlife sanctuary close to Nagapattinam town which offers tourists with a wide variety of interesting sites. The history of Nagapattinam can be clearly traced back to the rule of the Chola kings. During that time, the place was a famous port and trading centre. During the 3rd century King Ashoka had ordered the construction of a Buddha Vihar in the place, and it became a famous Buddhist centre during the 5th and the 6th century. The best time of the year to visit Nagapattinam is during October to March when the climatic conditions are at its best.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Nagapattinam houses a lot of hotels and lodges ranging from budget hotels to luxury hotels to suit all types of guests. Hotels in Nagapattinam are well equipped with a long list of essential facilities and amenities to provide high quality hospitality to the clients.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\n<strong>By Air</strong> - The closest airport to Nagapattinam is Tiruchirappalli which is located about 141 kms away. Taxis are available from Tiruchirappalli to Nagapattinam. Tiruchirappalli has regular flights to Chennai.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Nagapattinam has its own railway station and is connected by trains from major cities of South India. Thanjavur is a nearby railhead which is nicely connected to all the major parts of India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Nagapattinam is well connected by roads to Tamil Nadu as well as neighbouring states. Tamil Nadu State transport buses connect Nagapattinam to all major cities in the state. Private buses also regularly ply from Nagapattinam to Kerala, Karnataka and Andhra Pradesh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - The coastal town of Nagapattinam is principally connected by two national highways and they are NH 45A and NH 67.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Auto rickshaws, tourist cabs are easily available. Local buses are usually very crowded but also a cheap option.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(515, 14, 31, 1654, 'Tamil Nadu', 'INDIA', 'NAGERCOIL', 'sluice-202504_12802.jpg', 'sluice-202504_12803.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Nagercoil, a quiet and peaceful town in the state of Tamil Nadu lies very close to Kanyakumari and is located near the tip of the Indian Peninsula and is the farthest town in the south to be situated on the Indian mainland. This sleepy south Indian town is a popular destination among tourists because it has been blessed abundantly by Mother Nature, and thus has many beautiful and scenic spots that are alluring to the visitors coming from concrete jungles. According to legends, the place derives its name from the Nagaraja Temple that is located in the heart of the town. This temple has been an important place of worship for the Hindus from all over the state. The temple also attracts thousands of tourists each year. Some people believe that on the grounds of the temple once stood a Jain temple. People of the town are very proud of their rich historical past that is steeped in glory and bravery. History states that the town was part of the Travancore state for almost 10 years after India gained its Independence in 1947. It was only in 1956 that Nagercoil, along with Kanyakumari District, became part of the state of Tamil Nadu. During those days, the town was known as Nanjilnadu. The town has seen rulers belonging to different dynasties. The Cheras, the Cholas and the Pandyas have all known to rule over the town of Nagercoil. The kingdoms fought to gain control of this area since it was considered to be a very fertile land and thus ideal for farming and irrigation.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are different kinds of hotels located all around Nagercoil and everyone can choose the hotel as per their budget and requirement. Most of the hotels in Nagercoil offer all the basic amenities including clean and hygienic rooms, tea/coffee facility, television and a private bathroom. On the other hand most of the luxurious hotels offer many services including spa, swimming pool, bathtub, bathrobe, Jacuzzi, extra cot, welcome drink and many more apart from the basic amenities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - There is no airport at Nagercoil. The airport nearest to Nagercoil is the Thiruvanthapuram International Airport that is in Thiruvanthapuram, the capital of Kerala. The distance between the airport and Nagercoil is about 82 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Nagercoil is connected to the rest of the country by two railway stations; the Trivandrum Central and the Thirunelveli Junction. Trains from both the railway stations regularly run to Nagercoil.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - The town is connected to other major cities and towns in the state via a good network of roads. The town is connected to Kanyakumari, Kochi, Thiruvanthapuram and other cities. The Kerala State Bus Services run regular buses from the cities to Nagercoil. Deluxe buses as well as private cabs are also available.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - NAGERCOIL - (FAMOUS FOR KINNATHAPPAM IS A SWEET DISH &nbsp;MADE &nbsp;WITH WHITE RICE AND COCONUT MILK ; Theeyal IS SIMILAR TO SAMBHAR MADE FROM MIXTURE OF SPICES AND COOKED IN TAMARIND WATER WITH VEGETABLES ; Appam IS A TYPE OF &nbsp;PANCAKE MADE FROM RICE BATTER AND COCONUT MILK]&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(516, 14, 31, 1654, 'Tamil Nadu', 'INDIA', 'NAMAKKAL', 'ancient-265917_640.jpg', 'ancient-265917_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\nA city and an administrative district, Namakkal is one of the most popular tourist destinations of the southern part of India. Located in Tamil Nadu, Namakkal offers a wide range of attractions to people from varied interests. The city is renowned for its well maintained infrastructure and environment. It is famous as a historical city, an educational city, a Poultry city and Transport city. It officially became a district in 1997 after it was separated from Salem district. The history of Namakkal dates back to the 7th century. Namakkal has many temples and shrines for a tourist to offer for a visit. The Namakkal Dhurgam Fort is another tourist hotspot. The Rockfort and Naina Malai are other popular tourist hubs. The city derives its name from Namagiri, which is a single rock formation at the centre of the city. Namakkal was a part of Kongu Nadu region of Tamil Nadu. The city was ruled by King Gunaseela of Adiyaman clan. It has numerous historical relics such as the Ranganatha Swamy Temple and Narasimha Swamy Temple built by King Gunaseela. His marriage relations with the Pallava Dynasty resulted in the architectural influence. Later the kingdom was overrun by the Cholas and followed by the Hoysalas till the 14th century. Like the rest of South India, Namakkal experiences severe summer climate, hence the best time to visit the city is after the monsoons, during the months of October to March when the temperature is moderate.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">For a pilgrimage destination, Namakkal is well equipped with hotels to accommodate all types of guests who are visiting the town from all over the world, throughout the year.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Triuchirapalli Airport is the closest airport to Namakkal. Triuchirapalli, an international airport, is located 74 kms away from Namakkal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The nearest railhead is currently located in Salem and Karur which are connected to all major cities in the country. Buses and taxis are available from Salem and Karur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Namakkal is well connected by road and travelling to Namakkal by road is relatively easy. Buses are available from every big and small city in Tamil Nadu as well as some of the cities of Karnataka and Kerala.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SABAS CAFE, LOCATED AT NAMAKKAL RD, NEAR ELANGO MARRIAGE HALL, K K NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR BEETROOT CAKE, KULUKI SARBATH, CHICKEN SANDWICH)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '');
