(517, 14, 31, 1654, 'Tamil Nadu', 'INDIA', 'PERAMBALUR', 'truck-179638_6403.jpg', 'truck-179638_6404.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Perambalur is an administrative district in the state of Tamil Nadu, India. The district headquarters is located at Perambalur and occupies an area of 1752 sq kms. Perambalur district is a centrally located inland district of Tamil Nadu. It was trifurcated from the erstwhile composite Tiruchirappalli district and was formed on 1 November 1995. The district is bounded by Cuddalore district in the north, Tiruchirappalli district in the south, Ariyalur in the east and Namakkal and Tiruchirappalli districts in the west. The district lies in the Southern plateau &amp; hill zone of Agro climate regional planning with characteristics of semi arid climate. And also the world class Black Granite in Pachai malai Hills. The soil is predominantly red loamy and black soil. Cauvery is the major river flowing in the region and the composite district has a canal system covering just 47 kms stretch. The Flora and Fauna of the district are fairly rich and varied. As regards Fauna, big animals like Elephants and Bisons are not found in the district whereas spotted deer wild boars, Peacocks, Common monkeys, Jackals, Poisonous and non poisonous snakes etc.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Hotels in Perambalur are marvellously designed to cater the hi-end needs of leisure explorers in Perambalur. Guests can get accommodated in any of its comfortable multiple choice rooms. Other modern room amenities are available within the budget hotels in Perambalur. Visitors are offered room service by well trained and polite staff members. Day trippers to the city of can enjoy their stay with loved ones. For guests, parking is complimentary.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Instead of Perambalur tourists can a get flight to Civil Airport, Tiruchirapalli about 52 kms away, on regular basis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - There are no regular trains from other major cities to Perambalur. Nearest train station is Ariyalur 22 kms from Perambalur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Perambalur is an important road junction on the Chennai Madurai National Highways 45. The District has well knit road system connecting various important centres in the region.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Perambalur is well connected to other major cities of the country via regular buses. Private as well as government buses are available from Chennai, Madurai and other cities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - BANANA LEAF RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT SH 142, THURAI MANGALAM, THURAIMANGALAM - (FAMOUS FOR BUTTER CHICKEN AND &nbsp;MUTTON BIRIYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - ASWINS SWEETS &amp; SNACKS, LOCATED AT NEW BUS STAND ROAD, THURAIMANGALAM - (FAMOUS FOR SHAKES AND COFFEE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - UDAIYAR, &nbsp;LOCATED AT POST OFFICE SALAI, SUPER NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR BAJJI IS A SPICY SNACK MADE FROM GRAM FLOUR, VEGETABLES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - MARIAPPAN KADAI, LOCATED AT SALEM - PERAMBALUR ROAD, ATTUR - (FAMOUS FOR ONION UTTAPAM​ &nbsp;IS A DISH)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(518, 14, 31, 1654, 'Tamil Nadu', 'INDIA', 'PUDUKKOTTAI', 'road-243242_640.jpg', 'road-243242_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Pudukkottai is one of the Indian great places to visit during the holidays. This town is rich in history and this is evidence when one comes across amazing features such as ancient temples and other old structures carved by nature. The existence of Pudukkotai town dates back in 1673-1708 AD whereby according to history it was ruled by Raghunatha Thondaiman who fought wars and conquered other places Thirukkattupalli. There after it was ruled by Raya Thondaiman before it became a formal British protectorate. Pudukkotai tourist attraction sites include: Tonamil Nadu, Pillayarpatti, Karaikudi, Kodumbalur, Sittannavasal and many others. It also attracts many religious lovers may be due to abundant temples such as Muvar Koil, Thayumanavar Temple Kundrakudi Temple among others. Puddukottai, one of the most important districts of Tamil Nadu is surrounded by a number of important Tamilian districts including Tiruchirapalli and Thanjavur. An important district of Tamil Nadu, a tour to Puddukottai is a must include if you are planning a trip to Tamil Nadu. One of the most important influences in shaping the history of Tamil Nadu, Puddukottai has always played a pivotal role in determining the politics and future of Tamil Nadu. Thus a tour to Puddukottai can help in reconstructing the historical journey of not just Puddukottai but also that of Tamil Nadu as a whole. An erstwhile princely state, Puddukottai has been the centre of power for a number of ruling dynasties like the Pandyas, Cholas, Pallavas, Hoysalas, Vijayanagar, Nayaks, Irukkuvelirs, Mutharaiyars as well as the Thondaiman rulers.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are different kinds of hotels located all around Pudukkottai and everyone can choose the hotel as per their budget and requirement. Guests can enjoy the onsite bar. Free Wi-Fi is offered throughout the property and free private parking is available on site.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport to Pudukkottai is Trichy International Airport, which is approximately 55 kms from Pudukkottai.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Located in the Nainar Colony in Pudukkottai town, Pudukkottai railway station serves the population of district of Pudukkottai. The railway station come under the under the functional ambit of Madurai Railway Division. The Pudukkottai railway station is a significant passing station located on the Trichy Karaikkudi railroad line.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Several state highways and national highways connect Pudukkottai to the rest of the parts of the country. The two national highways that pass through Pudukkottai include NH 210 and NH 226.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Puddukottai is well connected to a number of neighbouring cities by an efficient network of roads. Tamil Nadu State transport buses connect Pudukkottai to all major cities in the state.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - APPUS CURIS FAMILY RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT POONGA NAGAR, RAJAGOPALAPURAM, RAILWAY STATION ROAD, NEAR STATE, BANK - (FAMOUS FOR MUTTON KEEMA CURRY AND SAMOSA CHAT)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - PRABU CANTEEN, LOCATED AT 1, N MAIN STREET, WADAIR SANTHA, BRINDAVAN - (FAMOUS FOR DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - MAHARAJA BAKERY, LOCATED AT 1ST ST, MARTHANDAPURAM - (FAMOUS FOR BUTTER BISCUIT AND CAKE)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(519, 14, 31, 1654, 'Tamil Nadu', 'INDIA', 'SIVAKASI (RAJAPALYAM)', 'fireworks-180553_640.jpg', 'fireworks-180553_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Sivakasi is a city well renowned for its industries dealing with fireworks and matchboxes. It is located in Virudhunagar district of Tamil Nadu. It is also one of the budding tourist destinations in the terms that it houses some of the most important temples and celebrates some colourful local festivals during different seasons. The history of Sivakasi is about 600 years old. King Harikesari Parakkirama Pandian, the ruler of Southern Madurai of which Sivakasi was a part, bought a Shiva lingam from Kasi to this part of his kingdom. Hence, the place sanctified by the Shivalingam from Kasi came to be known by the name of Sivakasi. Later King Pandia and King Thirumalai Naicker expanded the famous Shiva temple known as Kasi Viswanatha Swamy. Today it has become a famous attraction for tourists and devotees alike. Sivakasi experiences extremely hot and dry weather almost throughout the year, especially during the months of April to June. Hence it is not advisable to visit the city during the summer months. The best time of the year to visit Sivakasi is during the months of October to March.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Being an industrial town that receives business travellers from all over the country and a decent tourist destination, the town of Sivakasi is well equipped with a lot of good lodging services who provide quality accommodation options to the visitors.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The Madurai airport which is located at a distance of 74 km is the closest airport to Sivakasi. Madurai is well connected to most other major cities of India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Sivakasi is well connected by road. National Highway 47 that runs from Madurai to Trivandrum passes through Sivakasi.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>By Bus</strong> - Buses run at regular intervals from the various towns and cities of Tamil Nadu to Sivakasi. Private as well as government buses are available from Chennai, Madurai and other cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Sivakasi railways station is well connected to many places in Tamil Nadu such as Chennai, Rajapalayam, Tirunelveli, Madurai and Sengottai. Trains from Chennai to Sivakasi are not expensive however it is advisable to book tickets well in advance.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - ANANDA VILAS,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT 815, TENKASI RD, THOPPUPATTI&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; - (FAMOUS FOR BRIYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - PIZZAKAARAN, LOCATED AT SRI KALISWARI LE ORCHIDS, 5A, CHAIRMAN SHANMUGAM ROAD, KALIAPPA NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZAS)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(520, 14, 31, 1654, 'Tamil Nadu', 'INDIA', 'SALEM', 'road-390960_640.jpg', 'road-390960_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Salem is a city located in the North Central part of the south Indian state, Tamil Nadu. Located at a distance of 340 kms away from the capital city of Chennai, Salem is also famous as the Mango City. It is the fifth largest city in the state and a Municipal Corporation. The city derives its name from the word Cheram which indicates that the region is a part of Cheram land. The ancient profession of the inhabitants of the region was to weave Saeylai which is a cloth worn by women. Salem is counted as the fifth biggest city in Tamil Nadu state in terms of population after Chennai, Coimbatore, Madurai and Tiruchirappalli &nbsp;respectively. Salem is the main city of western Tamil Nadu. The city is located at the base of beautiful Yercaud hills. The city is one of the major producers of traditional silver anklets that are quite popular among women. Major industries of the city are textile, steel, automotive and poultry. The city has one of the largest magnetite ore deposits in the country. Some of the leading companies such as Dalmia and Tanmag have mines here. Leigh Bazaar is famous as a large regional market for agro products. Apart from its steel industries, mango orchids, scenic tourist attractions and religious shrines, the city also boasts of Modern Theatre which was the first ever cinema hall in India. Adding more to its merits, Salem is supposedly the birth place of the famous Tamil Poetess Avvaiyar. It is the perfect summer escape for tourists with famous hill station like Yercaud lying in its constituency. So visit Salem and experience life in the lap of the nature.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Visitors will get outstanding lodging facilities in Salem. The hotels here ensure best accommodation in Salem. Tourists will get best dining, accommodation and other leisure facilities which will make entire vacation just amazing. Apart from lodging, here one can also do shopping and can explore famous attractions of the city which will make the entire holyday trip unforgettable.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Salem can be reached easily by air through the Salem Airport. Direct flights Fly to and from the major cities of the country and one can reach Salem easily.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>By Road</strong> - Salem is very well connected to other cities through neat, clean and well maintained roads. Many national highways also link the city to other destinations and thus can be reached via cabs, personal cars and buses.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>By Train </strong>- There are regular trains operating from Salem railway station to other parts of the country that can be used to reach Salem via rail link. Salem Junction, Pedanayakanpalayam and Salem Town are the main stations from where one can reach Salem and vice-versa.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SALEM - [FAMOUS FOR PORI URUNNDAI IS SWEET CRISPY AND LIGHT MADE OF PUFFED RICE ; CABBAGE PORIYAL IS A SPICED DISH MADE FROM STEAMED CABBAGE ALONG WITH SAMBAR RICE ; KUZHAMBU IS AKIND OF SOUP &nbsp;MADE FROM LENTILS, TAMARIND AND VEGETABLES ; MANGO RASAM IS A SWEET AND TANGY ; GARLIOC RASAM IS ASPICY AND SOUR DISH MADE OF GARLIC AND CHILLIES ; POORI MASALA IS A DISH MADE WITH POTATOES, FLOUR LENTILS &nbsp;FRIED IN OIL AND SERVED WITH GREEN CHILLY CHUTNEY ; PAYA IS AN HOT DISH MADE OF LAMP AND GOAT MEAT]&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(521, 14, 31, 1654, 'Tamil Nadu', 'INDIA', 'SIVAGANGAI', 'truck-253151_640.jpg', 'truck-253151_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">A town in Tamil Nadu, Sivagangai is the administrative headquarters of the Sivagangai District. Found by Sasivarnana Periya Udaya Thevar, the first king of Sivagangai dynasty, Sivagangai is the capital of Chettinad. It is so because of the predominance of the Nattu Kottai Chettiars of Chettinad who ventured far and wide from here to establish their trade even at the turn of the 20th century. Sivagangai is located on the south east of Madurai. Tour to Sivagangai will reveal more about the glorious past of this town which was founded by Sasivarnana Periya Udaya Thevar. The remnants of these palaces can be seen here in Sivagangai. There is the Sree Vishwanatha and Sree Subramanya Temples also in Sivagangai. The Tepakkulam or tank adds to the splendor of the house. Sivagangai is a wonderful small town which has the remnants of its glorious past. Founded by Sasivarnana Periya Udaya Thevar, he was considered to the first king of the Sivagangai dynasty. There is the Sree Vishwanatha and Sree Subramanya Temples also in Sivagangai which are considered to be the palace of the erstwhile rulers.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">BNR lodge is one of the best located nearby Sivagangai railway station. BNR is one of the family safe hotels with all good facilities along with marriage hall. Hotel Shanmugabhavan is another hotel with food and accommodation facility located in the heart of Sivagangai bus stand.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport is the Madurai Airport 60 kms from Sivagangai.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Rail</strong> - The main railway station is located at Madurai.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road </strong>- Sivaganga is 45 kms east of Madurai, from where tourists can avail of frequent Government and Private Buses.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - SIVAGANGAI - [FAMOUS FOR KOZHUKKATTA IS A SWEET MADE FROM RICE FLOUR, &nbsp;FILLING WITH GRATED COCONUT AND JAGGERY ; PADDU IS A DISH MADE BT STEAMING BATTER USING A MOULD ; ADHIRASAM IS AN INDIAN SWEET MADE WITH RICE FLOUR AND JAGGERY]&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(522, 14, 31, 1654, 'Tamil Nadu', 'INDIA', 'THANJAVUR', 'brihadeeswara-temple-989323_1280.jpg', 'brihadeeswara-temple-989323_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Thanjavur is a municipality located in the district of the same name that consists of six sub districts. Thanjavur rose to importance during the rule of the Chola Kings, who saw fit to make it their capital. Thanjavur, the country&rsquo;s centre of culture towards the end of the 18th century, maintains a reputation for being a hotspot for huge hordes of pilgrimages as well as thousands of tourist year in and year out. It is interesting that while most of the Thanjavur Maratha kingdom was added on to the British Raj in 1799, the Marathas held rights upon the palace and the fort surrounding it. The name Thanjavur is believed by a group of scholars to have originated from the word Tanjan. Tanjan is a prominent demon in Hindu Mythology. The Hindu God, Vishnu, is understood to have killed the demon or the asura at the spot where the town exists and granted the demon&rsquo;s last wish which was to name the town there named after him. Thanjavur also serves as the base for the Tyagaraja Aradhana, a music festival held every year during the months of January and February. The Pongal Festival is held from the 14th to the 16th of January as well. The main occupation of the residents of Thanjavur is tourism and service, while the traditional occupation from days gone by has been agriculture. Known as the rice bowl of Tamil Nadu, Thanjavur is home to the cultivation and harvesting of crops such paddy, coconut, sugarcane, etc. The climate in Thanjavur follows the same pattern as most other cities nearby and is primarily hot and humid during summer. The rainfall in the South west monsoon pales in comparison to the rain received during the North east monsoon. The latter is of assistance to the district as the Western Ghats feed the Cauvery River during this time.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Thanjavur gives a tourist a lot of options among deluxe and medium budget hotels and accommodation places. The hotels provide good services to their guests. There are a number of deluxe hotels and moderate budget hotels in Thanjavur.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The closest International Airport to Thanjavur is in Trichy at a distance of around 61 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Trichy Junction is the closest railhead, and is located 58 kilometres from Thanjavur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Thanjavur is connected with major cities in Tamil Nadu by private tourist buses as well as those of the Tamil Nadu Road Transport Corporation. Regular bus services exist from Trichy and Madurai to Thanjavur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Auto rickshaw, tourist cabs, cycle rickshaws are available.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - THANJAVUR - [FAMOUS FOR KOOTU IS A DISH MADE OF VEGETABLES AND LENTILS ; KUZHAMBU IS A SOUP &nbsp;MADE FROM &nbsp;LENTILS, TAMARIND AND VEGETABLES ; MOR KUZHAAMBU IS A CURRY MADE OF LENTILS AND SERVED WITH BOILED RICE, PANCAKE]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(523, 14, 31, 1654, 'Tamil Nadu', 'INDIA', 'THE NILGIRIS', 'tea-plantation-1751369_640.jpg', 'tea-plantation-1751369_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The district of Nilgiris is a very famous tourist destination in the state of Tamil Nadu in India and people from different parts of the country and also from outside the country visits this district throughout the year. Udhagamandalam, the headquarters of the Nilgiris district, is the largest and most important hill station in south India. This principle station on the Nilgiris is at an elevation of 2286 mts and located at the centre of the district. It is an extensive valley enclosed on all sides but the west by a lofty range of hills. The Nilgiri Hills are part of a larger mountain chain known as the Western Ghats. Nilgiris, one of the oldest mountain ranges, located at the tri junction of Tamil Nadu, Kerala and Karnataka. Nilgiris is a part of the Western Ghats. Ooty the queen of hill stations, Coonoor 19 kms from Ooty and Kotagiri 31 kms from Ooty, are the three hill stations of this district. Nilgiris is India&#39;s first biosphere. It has been declared as one of the 14 hotspots of the world because of its unique bio diversity. Rolling grasslands, dense sholas, waterfalls, streams, lakes, vast expanse of tea plantations, interspersed with vegetable gardens, spectacular view points, an amazing variety of flora and fauna, fabulous trekking trails, innumerable heritage sites, spell binding sunrises and sunsets, magical light, pollution free atmosphere, mist, clouds, fog, star studded skies, serenity etc. The name Nilgiris means Blue hills the first mention of this name has been found in the Silappadikaram. There is a belief that the people living in the plains at the foot of the hills should have given the name, the Nilgiris in view of the violet blossoms of kurinji flower enveloping the hill ranges periodically. Nilgiris presents a truly breathtaking kaleidoscope of visual treats and soul stirring experiences.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Nilgiris has a lot of deluxe and medium to budget accommodation options in the nearby region. There are deluxe accommodations with all high class facilities which make the stay a reliable and memorable one. Ooty is a hospitable town with innumerable hotels of star status, budget hotels and time share resorts to suit every tourist&#39;s pocket.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest International Airport is Coimbatore International Airport, roughly three hour drive from Nilgiris. Coimbatore Airport is well connected to the places in India and abroad.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The nearest Railway Station is Ooty Railway Station from Nilgiris. Ooty Railway Station is connected to all the major cities of Tamil Nadu. It is situated on the major New Delhi-Chennai railway line and is linked with the major cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - The Nagapattinam Gudalur National Highway passes through this district. The Nilgiri Ghat Roads link Nilgiris with nearby cities in Tamil Nadu, Kerala and Karnataka. All the taluks are connected with major roads.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Ooty bus stand serves as the central bus stand for the district, along with Municipal Bus Stand, Coonoor. All kinds of AC, Non-AC, deluxe and semi deluxe buses are available in the district.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SYEDI, LOCATED AT NILGIRIS, UPPER BAZAAR, OOTY - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;KABAB)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - CLIFF TOP, LOCATED AT WELBECK CIRCLE, CLUB ROAD, NILGIRIS DISTRICT, OOTY - (FAMOUS FOR ROAST LAMB,KASHMIRI CHICKEN KADHAI, DAL MAKHNI AND CHOCOLATE BROWNIE)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - HOTEL JUNIOR KUPPANNA, LOCATED AT COMMERCIAL ROAD, NEAR CHARRING CROSS JUNCTION, UPPER BAZAAR - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;CHICKEN CURRY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - QUALITY RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT CORONATION AVENUE, CHURCH HILL ROAD, OOTY&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; - (FAMOUS FOR PARTHA WITH VINDALO ( IS A TYPE OF CURRY MADE FROM VINEGAR, SUGAR, GINGER, SPICES, CHILI PEPPERS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - HOTEL TAJ, LOCATED AT 55, COMMERCIAL RD, UPPER BAZAAR, OOTY - (FAMOUS FOR BEEF BIRYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - AMMA&#39;S KITCHEN, LOCATED AT ROHINI JUNCTION,MYSORE ROAD, KANDAL, OOTY - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN TIKKA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - GREEN FIELDS, LOCATED AT HAREWOOD ROAD, ALWARPET, COONOOR - (FAMOUS FOR MUTTON BRIYANI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n8 - OOTY COFFEE HOUSE,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT 2ND FLOOR, COMMERCIAL ROAD, UPPER BAZAR ROAD, OOTY - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;SOUTH INDIAN FOOD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>9 - WILLY&#39;S CAFE, LOCATED AT 1ST FLOOR, KCR ARCADE, WALSHAM ROAD, UPPER BAZAAR - (FAMOUS FOR CAKES, SANDWICHES AND FRENCH FRIES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>10 - PRABHA SWEETS, LOCATED AT COMMERCIAL ROAD, UPPER BAZAAR, OOTY - (FAMOUS FOR RABDI &nbsp;IS A SWEET MADE FROM MILK AND SUGAR, AND &nbsp;GULABJAMUN)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(524, 14, 31, 1654, 'Tamil Nadu', 'INDIA', 'THIRUVALLUR', 'india-317_1280.jpg', 'india-317_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Thiruvallur district is an administrative district in the South Indian state of Tamil Nadu.It is a part of Greater Chennai Corporation. The town of Tiruvallur is the district headquarters. The district has a mixture of urban and rural characteristics. The Eastern part of Tiruvallur district is dominated by urban characteristics while the Southern and Northern part of the district has influence of Andhra culture due to its position. Tiruvallur was originally known as Tiruvallur which specifies the sleeping position of the holy lord Balaji, in the Veeraragava temple of Tiruvallur. Later people began to refer it by names such as Trivellore and Tiruvallur. Today Tiruvallur is well known, one of the reasons being the Veeraragava Temple. The new moon day is very auspicious day for the lord and so for the people of the town. It is bounded on the north by Andhra Pradesh state, on the east by the Bay of Bengal, on the southeast by Chennai district, on the south by Kanchipuram and on the west by Vellore district. The coastal region of the district is mostly flat and dreary; but in the other parts it is undulating and even hilly in some places. The place is mainly known for the number of temples and tourists come here to worship mainly. The main temples here are Veera Raghavar Temple, Shri Viswarupa Panchamukha Hanumana Temple, Kakkalur hanuman Temple, Sri Pushavaneshwarar Temple and Shiva Vishnu Temple. The churches here include the CSI Goudie Memorial Church, St. Francis De Sale Church, Miracle AG Church, Shalom Prayer Tower and many more.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>When planning to visit the temple town of Thrivallur, tourists can find a comfortable hotel for the stay from the following list of hotels.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - Instead of Tiruvallur tourists can a get flight to Chennai Airport on regular basis which is 34 kms away.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train </strong>- There are regular trains from other major cities of the country to Tiruvallur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - The Metropolitan Transport Corporation (MTC) operates frequent bus service from Thiruvallur to Chennai city and the Chennai Metropolitan area.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - PERAMBUR SRI SRINIVASA SWEETS AND SNACKS, LOCATED AT SH 50, MGM NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR SOUTH INDIAN FOOD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - ROYAL FAMILY RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT 1ST FLOOR, MADRAS THIRUVALLUR HIGH ROAD, SHANTHI NAGAR, KUMARASAMY COLONY, PADI - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN CURRY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - SINGAPORE FAST FOOD, LOCATED AT &nbsp;M.T.H ROAD, CHENNAI TIRUVALLUR HIGH ROAD, ANNA NAGAR WEST, PADI - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;NOODLES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - THALAPAKATTU, LOCATED AT JN ROAD, HARIRAM NAGAR, V.M NAGAR, PERIYAKUPPAM - (FAMOUS FOR BIRYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - KOLKATA MITHAI BHAVAN, LOCATED AT CHITRA SHOPPING INN, CHOOLAIMEDU HIGH ROAD, THIRUVALLUVAR PURAM - (FAMOUS FOR RASAGULA &nbsp;AND LAADU)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - PERAMBUR SRINIVASA, LOCATED AT SH 50, KUMARAVEL NAGAR, SP NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR MILK SWEETS)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(525, 14, 31, 1654, 'Tamil Nadu', 'INDIA', 'THOOTHUKUDI (TUTICORIN)', 'yoga-1996209_640.jpg', 'yoga-1996209_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Thoothukudi, also popularly known as Tuticorin, is the Municipal Corporation of the district by the same name. Located in the south eastern coast of the State of Tamil Nadu, it is a famous port town. The city is famous for its pearl diving, hence has also been christened as Pearl town. The city is also famous for fishing and shipbuilding. On the northern and western side of Thoothukudi lies Tirunelveli district and to its east are Ramanathapuram and Virudhunagar. The capital city of Tamil Nadu Chennai is located at a distance of 600 kms of from Thoothukudi city. The city is also close to Trivandrum which is located at a distance of 190 kms. For the lovers of the sea, Thoothukudi is the ideal tourist destination. The port of the city is one of the most important and attractive tourist sites. The city is also popular for its parks the most popular out of them are the Harbour Park, Rajaji Park and Roche Park. The city is also famous for the Tiruchendur temple which has been dedicated to Lord Subramanya. The city is also famous for the Central Marine Fisheries Research Institute. The famous rock cut Jain temple Kalugumalai, Korkai Tank and Vettrivelamman temple are also popular tourist attractions. The latter two are also famous picnic spots. Thoothukudi was known as Thiru Mandir Nagar in the past. Legends say that the Hanuman had camped in Thoothukudi on his way to Lanka while he was searching for Sita. The name of the city is also said to have derived from the word Thoothan which means messenger. The best time of the year to visit the city is during the winters in the months of October to March, when the temperature is mild and pleasant.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are numerous Hotels available. Being a major city, hotels are available for every price range. Most of the hotels are concentrated on the V.E road and Bus stand road but are available on Beach Road as well.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Thoothukudi airport is located at a distance of around 14 kms away from the city. The airport is connected to Chennai Airport.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The Thoothukudi railway station is a major railway station. Regular trains operate from here to cities like Mysore, Chennai, Madurai and Coimbatore to name a few. Trains make the city easily accessible.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - There are numerous highways, including National Highway 45B, 7A and various state highways run through the city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Thoothukudi is connected to most other cities of south India by buses. These buses ply on a regular basis and make the city extremely accessible. The buses are cheap, and the ideal option to reach the city. Regular buses are also available from Chennai and other places.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water</strong> - Travelling by Sea is yet another option. Tuticorin accepts cargo from all over the country. It is also one of the only ports that ship cargo to the USA directly. Some of these ships also carry passengers. But travelling by sea often proves to be more expensive and is hence avoided.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Being a major city of Tamil Nadu, getting buses or cabs is very easy. Bus stands are spread all over the city. Also, cabs and auto rickshaws are available outside every major tourist spot. Various Hotels and Motels can also arrange for cabs, to take around all day, on request.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - THOOTHUKUDI - [FAMOUS FOR ULUTHAM KALI IS ASWEET MADE FROM BLACK URAD DAL, RICE, PALM, SUGAR &nbsp;AND GRANTED COCONUT ; TUTICORIN MACAROONS IS A SWEET MADE FROM CASHEW &nbsp; GROUND ALMONDS OR COCONUT ; VENDHAYA KALI IS vegetarian DISH SERVED IN BREAKFAST MADE FROM RICE, FENUGREEK, JIGGERY ; VATHAL KULAMBU IS A TYPE OF VATTHA CURRY MADE FROM SUNDAKKA, ONIONS, TAMARIND, GARLIC AND JIGGERY ; KARUVADU KULAMBU IS A DRY FISH CURRY MADE FROM FISH, COCONUT MILK AND SPICES coconut milk AND SPICES ; MEEN VARUVAL IS A FISH FRY MADE FROM COCONUT, ONION, CUMIN SEEDS AND MIXTURE OF SPICES]&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(526, 14, 31, 1654, 'Tamil Nadu', 'INDIA', 'TRICHY (TIRUCHIRAPPALLI)', 'temple-52053_640.jpg', 'temple-52053_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Trichy or Tiruchirappalli is an industrial and educational city in the south Indian state of Tamil Nadu. Trichy is the administrative headquarters of the district by the same name. The city is located on the banks of the river Kaveri. The city is the fourth largest Municipal Corporation and urban agglomeration of Tamil Nadu. There are several contemplations about the origin of the name of the place. The name Tiruchirappalli is derived from the Sanskrit word Trishirapuram which is comes from the two words Trishira which means three heads and palli or puram which means city. It is believed that the three headed demon Trishira prayed to Lord Shiva near the city and obtained favours. A rock inscription from the 16th century has mentioned Tiruchirappalli as Tiru ssila palli which means Holy rock town. During the rule of the British, Tiruchirappalli was referred to as Trichinopoly which has been shortened to Trichy or Tiruchi. The city of Trichy is one of the oldest places to have been inhabited in Tamil Nadu. It has a rich cultural heritage and has seen the rise and fall of several empires. The earliest settlements were traced around the 2nd millennium BC. The early Chola kings ruled the place in the 3rd century BC. In the medieval era, the Pallava king Mahendravarman I who ruled the place in the 6th century AD constructed several cave temples in Rockfort. The rich cultural heritage and tradition has resulted in presenting Trichy with some of the most splendid historical religious places and fortresses. The winters in Trichy are cooler and pleasant. The winter months between November and February are also the best time of the year to visit the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Much as expected, Trichy has numerous hotels to offer its visitors. Even if arrive without a prior booking, tourists can be sure that they will easily find a room of their choice, irrespective of the budget. The Hotels are largely near the bus terminus area and the Airport Area.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Trichy has own and world&#39;s 10th busiest airport named as Tiruchirapalli International Airport about 5 kms away from the city centre. Trichy Airport is connected to Chennai and Bangalore as well as Sri Lanka and Kuala Lumpur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The Trichy Junction is one of the major railway stations in south India. Regular trains from Trichy are available to Madurai, Chennai, Bangalore, Mumbai and Tirupati. So visiting this place via train is a good option.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Trichy is well connected to National Highway 45 and 67 via road. So, one can easily get in here by hired taxi or private vehicle.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Trichy is easily accessible by bus as Tamil Nadu State Transport Corporation (TNSTC) buses serve a good service from major cities. Private buses also ply regularly to cities like Trivandrum and Bangalore. The buses are a cheap and comfortable option to travel to Trichy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - The city has an extensive network of transportation facilities. The Local buses and auto rickshaws are the most common ways of commuting. In addition to those, taxis are easy to find. Special arrangements can also be made from hotel, on payment of extra charges.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - TIRUCHIRAPPALI(TRICHY) - [FAMOUS FOR PORIYAL IS MADE FROM VEGETABLES ALONG WITH SPICES ; MYSORE PAK IS A sweet DISH MADE FROM &nbsp;GHEE, SUGAR, GRAM FLOUR AND OFTEN CARDAMOM ; APPALAM IS IN &nbsp;CRISPY TASTE MADE FROM PEELED GRAM FLOUR]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(527, 14, 31, 1654, 'Tamil Nadu', 'INDIA', 'TIRUNELVELI', 'india-995576_6406.jpg', 'india-995576_6407.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The city was known as Nellai during the British rule and is an ancient city in the state of Tamil Nadu. The city came under the rule of the Pandya Kings who ruled the region around 600 BC and later came under the rule of the Chola dynasty. Tirunelveli also came under the colonial British Empire in India and was under the rule of the Nawab of the Carnatic and a part of the princely Carnatic state. The city is located at the southernmost tip of the Deccan plateau and due to its natural and costal surroundings is also a home to a wide variety of flora and fauna. Tirunelveli is a big city in the midst of numerous small towns, each with its own bounty of beautiful sights, temples, waterfalls and much more. Unlike many temple towns, it also does offer many other sites to its tourists, including some breath taking waterfalls. Though it is one of the largest cities in Tamil Nadu and has a booming agrarian economy, Tirunelveli is far from being a regular commercial hub. It has its roots very much intact, with multiple religious splendours waiting to be discovered. An amazing tourist destination, Tirunelveli is located in the state of Tamil Nadu which was widely known as Nellai and Tinnevelly during the British rule. It is one of the sixth largest cities of Tamil Nadu and is divided in four zones named as Thatchanallur Zone, Palayamkottai Zone, Melapalayam Zone and Tirunelveli Zone. Tirunelveli Travel guide is incomplete without a mention of its religious destinations, natural beauty and rich heritage. &nbsp;Tirunelveli is positioned close to the southern tip of India and is very eminent for various geographical features. It comprises of 5 geographical territories which include Kurinji Mountains, Marudham paddy fields, Neithal coastal, Mullai forests and Palai deserts.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Tirunelveli has multiple accommodation options, with tariffs ranging from a few hundreds to a few thousands a night. Though these hotels and guest houses are spread all over the city, a lot of them are concentrated around Madurai Road.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Tirunelveli does not have an airport of its own, but travelling by plane is as convenient as any other mode. The nearest airport is the Tuticorin Airport and is under 42 kms away.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- The area has an extensive network of roadways. Located on NH 7, Tirunelveli has a state run bus service and overnight and day buses are available from various places. It is located about 70 kms north of Kanyakumari.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Unlike an airport, Tirunelveli has its own railway station the Tirunelveli Junction Railway Station. The station is one of the largest in Tamil Nadu and has trains coming in from almost every corner of the state.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Being a major city of Tamil Nadu, Tirunelveli does not have any problems when it comes to intra city commuting. Taxis and rickshaws are very easy to find. The intra city bus services are very efficient. Buses are run by the Tirunelveli Municipal Corporation and bus stands are spread out all over the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - TIRUNELVELI - [FAMOUS FOR KUZHI PANIYARAM IS A DISH MADE BY BATTER( IS BLACK LENTILS AND RICE)]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(528, 14, 31, 1654, 'Tamil Nadu', 'INDIA', 'KANYAKUMARI (TIRUPUR)', 'kanyakumari-847081_6401.jpg', 'kanyakumari-847081_6402.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kanyakumari, which was famous as Cape Comorin in the past, is situated in Tamil Nadu, India. The town is located at the southernmost tip of Indian mainland. Kanyakumari rests at the position where the Indian Ocean, the Bay of Bengal and the Arabian Sea join. The state of Kerala is situated towards its northwest and west, whereas the Tirunelveli district is located towards its north and east. The capital of Kerala, that is Thiruvanathapuram, is located at almost 85 kilometres from Kanyakumari. The town is also well known for its eye catching and magnificent dawns and dusks, particularly on the full moon days. Kanyakumari was called Cape Comorin in British times. Kanyakumari is also spelled as Kanniyakumari or Kanniakumari. It is one of the famous tourist spots of India by virtue of being located at the southernmost point of Peninsular India. This town is bordered by colourful sea shores edged with swaying coconut trees that make it an ideal spot for travellers. This place is famous for its lofty patches of red cliffs with rolling valleys and plain areas between the rocky topography and the sea coast. The whole region is known for its rich history and cultural heritage which is a blend of diverse culture and profound inheritance. Two of the most famous things about this place are rocks known as twin rocks serving as monuments of Swami Vivekananda and Saint Thiruvalluvar. Thousands of people from all over the world come here to experience the place where one can watch the sunrise and sunset from a single beach because this place is almost surrounded by water.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are numerous hotels, residencies etc. in and around Kanyakumari and therefore, staying over is not be a problem. Vivekananda Kendra can be a good option for people looking for a decent, yet cheap accommodation, but it&#39;s around 3 kms from Kanyakumari. Hotel Sea View, Hotel Sangam and a couple of other hotels offer such rooms for 12 hrs. Note that many rooms are priced for 12 hrs and not per day especially during the peak season.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport to Kanyakumari is Trivandrum International airport, which is situated at a distance of 67 kms from Kanyakumari. From here on, buses and rental cars are easily available to reach Kanyakumari.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Kanyakumari is well connected with the major cities of South India by road. Tourists can opt for the self drive option else a number of Tamil Nadu and Kanyakumari road transport buses are available to Kanyakumari.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - Kanyakumari has its own railway station Kanyakumari railway station which is well connected from most of the major cities of India. The second closest railway station to the city is Trivandrum railway station.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Most people travel around Kanyakumari using a hired vehicle. Auto rickshaws, tuk tuks, etc. are available, along with buses. Local buses are also available from the bus station to the point.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - AROMA, LOCATED AT 74, KUMARAN ROAD, KANNIPIRAN COLONY, VALIPALAYAM - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;NORTH INDIAN FOOD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - LE ARABIA, LOCATED AT MAIN ROAD, KANYAKUMARI&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN PAROTTA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - SREE PUNJABI DHABA, LOCATED AT 1/1, OPP HOTEL SAGAR, SOUTH CAR STREET - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;ALOO PARATHA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - KANYAKUMARI (TIRUPUR) - {FAMOUS FOR PAYASAM IS A SWEET DISH MADE FROM RICE, MILK, SUGAR, CARDAMOM, SAFFRON, PISTACHIOS OR ALMONDS; RAVA KESARI IS A SWEET DISH MADE FROM SEMOLINA, SUGAR, SAFFRON OR FOOD COLOUR ; PONGAL IS A DISH MADE FROM RICE}</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(529, 14, 31, 1654, 'Tamil Nadu', 'INDIA', 'TIRUVANNAMALAI (DHARAMPURI)', 'india-1274609_640.jpg', 'india-1274609_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Dharmapuri city is situated in Tamil Nadu. The place is well known for its scenic beauty and adjacent places because the city is located close to Karnataka which is an adjacent state. The city is renowned for its various tourist attractions. Moreover, a lot of visitors from Bangalore and Chennai pay frequent visits to the place because Dharmapuri is situated roughly between Bangalore and Chennai. In ancient times, Dharmapuri was governed by many rulers like Cholas, Rashtrakutas and Pandyas. The well known Hogenakkal falls is located at the border of Tamil Nadu and Karnataka. This place is about 46 kms away from the city Dharmapuri. This is a perfect place where visitors can relax and allow the serene waters of the waterfall calm their minds. Another beautiful spot is Krishnagiri dam situated between Krishnagiri and Dharmapuri. Kottai Kovil, Chenraya Perumal Temple and Shri Theerthagirishwarar temple are famous temples of this place. The other attractions of Dharmapuri include Mount Carmel Church, C.S.I Zion Church and Sacred Heart Cathedral and Mettur dam. Adhiyamankottai is located about 7 kms away from Dharmapuri which contains ruins of a fort which is more or less oval in shape. Winter months are best for the travellers to visit this place.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Best places to put up when in Dharmapuri with family need to be good, safe and clean. The tariff in the hotels in Dharmapuri starts from Rs. 800 to Rs. 1000 depending on the type of room you choose. Accommodation is available in plenty both from Temple authorities and also from private hotels.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The airport which is in the vicinity of Dharmapuri is the Bangalore airport. Bangalore airport is located about 172 kilometres away from Dharmapuri. Both international as well as domestic flights are available from this airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The Dharmapuri railway station is well connected to the main cities like Kannur, New Delhi, Mysore, Tuticorina and Coimbatore via frequent trains. Trains are much cheaper as compared to bus services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - The city also has an excellent bus network, and visitors can avail buses to and from all the important cities which are located nearby. The major bus stand of the city is in Salem and visitors can avail frequent buses from here. All kinds of AC, Non-AC, deluxe and semi deluxe buses are available in Dharmapuri.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - PONNI MULTI CUISINE RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT 98, NETHAJI BYPASS ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR FISH FRY AND FRIED RICE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - AAHAA PALKHOVA, LOCATED AT KARAGURARMAPURI-KRISHNAGIRI ROAD, SAPPANIPATTI - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA AND COFFEE)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '');
