(530, 14, 31, 1654, 'Tamil Nadu', 'INDIA', 'VELLORE', 'vellore-774934_640.jpg', 'vellore-774934_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Vellore is known for being the transit hub for travellers. Popularly known as the Fort City of Tamil Nadu, Vellore has a splendid past with a harmonious fusion of rich culture and heritage and an everlasting legacy of the early Dravidian civilisation. Vellore is among the most renowned historical cities located in the state of Tamil Nadu. The city has a glorious past, which makes it more popular and it lies on the bank of the River Palar. Presently, a very serene and simple place, it was once a battlefield and has witnessed several wars. The name of the city means a city of spears. Vellore has an inspiring inheritance reflecting the early Dravidian culture. The well known Vellore Fort is considered to be the most influential fortress of its time and was constructed in the 16th century by the Nayakar group of leaders belonging to the Vijayanagar kingdom. It is totally made of granite blocks and the fort is at present a historical tourist hotspot. The city is also popular worldwide for having one of the best hospitals in India, the Christian Medical College and Hospital. It is located in the centre of the city and it is also one of the major private employers in the city. The other major Vellore attractions are the Jalakanteshwara Temple, Muthu Mandapam or the Pearl Palace and the Government Museum. Vellore, strikes immediately the famous VIT, Vellore Institute of Technologies and most beautiful ever The Golden temple. The Sripuram golden temple is the largest golden temple of the world that&rsquo;s interior and exterior with the idol of Mahalaxmi is made up of pure gold. The temple works as a major religious attraction among tourist. The historical Vellore fort is an added interest among the visitors. It is considered as the best military architectural structure of Southern India.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The accommodation facility in Vellore is highly developed because of the well established tourism industry. These hotels provide all the required facilities to the travellers for their comfort at a very reasonable rate. These are well maintained and comprise of a variety of amenities including hospitality, television, internet connectivity, telephone service and much more.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\n<strong>By Air</strong> - If travelling to Vellore by air, tourists have to alight at the Tirupati Airport which is nearest domestic airport at a distance of 120 kms. The Chennai International Airport which is 130 kms away and Bangalore International Airport that lies at a distance of 224 kms are the closest international airports.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Vellore has three main railway stations. The most important one is the Vellore Katpadi Junction. The second big station, Vellore Cantonment, is in Suriyakulam and 8 kms from the Katpadi Junction. The third and the smallest station is the Vellore Town Station. It lies in Konavattam connecting the Katpadi Junction with the Villipuram Junction.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Vellore is well connected with foremost towns in Tamil Nadu, Karnataka, Andhra Pradesh and rest of the Peninsular India with a mesh of state as well as nationwide highways. Vellore lies on NH 46 that connects Bangalore and Chennai. Vellore can be come to by NH 4 that connects Ranipet to Chennai and the Cuddalore Chittoor highway.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - The town has two coach terminals, namely the Town Bus Terminus and the Central coach Terminus. Buses are available from Chennai and Banglore.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n<strong>1 - VELLORE - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;PAAYASAM IS A SWEET DISH MADE OF VERMICELLI, MILK AND SUGAR ; MURRUKU OR CHAKLI IS A SNACK, MADE UP OF SEMOLINA, REFINED FLOUR AND RICE FLOUR ; THATTAI IS A SNACK MADE FROM RICE FLOUR]&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(531, 14, 31, 1654, 'Tamil Nadu', 'INDIA', 'VILLUPURAM', 'bus-276136_640.jpg', 'bus-276136_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Villupuram is the district headquarters of the Villuppuram District, which was bifurcated from the erstwhile composite Sourt Arcot District from 30th September, 1993. &nbsp; It is the Second largest District in the State which lies in the middle of the Tiruchirapalli to Chennai National Highways 45. This district is having variety of tourist spots which are more than 100 years old. The district has temples, masques and churches which are very old and famous. Nestled on three hills, and enclosed by a huge rampart 60 feet thick, stands the majestic Gingee Fort, in the Villuppuram district, which is located on the Thindivanam to Thiruvannamalai road about 25 kms from Thindivanam and 130 kms from Chidambaram. &nbsp;The indomitable courage and valour of its erstwhile rulers, caused Father Pimenta, a Jesuit priest to call the Gingee Fort the Troy of the East Besieged by the Mughals and battered by the British, the fort still stands at 800ft in height, guarded by a moat, eighty feet wide. Much of the early history of this 800 year old fort is shrouded in mystery, as the fort seems to have changed many hands times before it was annexed to the Vijayanagar Empire. Most of the structures, fortification walls and temples were built during this period. The fortifications and defences were further strengthened under Chatrapati Shivaji, the great Maratha ruler, was captured Gingee in 1677 AD. Gingee came under the hegemony of the Moghul emperor Aurangazeb in 1691 AD, and Sarup Singh was appointed as the chief of Gingee by the emperor, under the control of the Nawab of Arcot.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Vilupuram has a number of hotels to cater to the tourists and people coming for business. These hotels provide good quality service at attractive prices.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport to Villupuram is Chennai International Airport, Chennai which is 139 kms away from Villupuram city centre.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- The nearest railway station to Villupuram is Villupuram Junction Train Station which is 12 kms away from Villupuram city centre.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Vilupuram is well connected by roads to major cities and to the rest of the state. Villupuram has the longest National roads of any district in Tamil Nadu. NH 45 connects Chennai to Theni via Viluppuram and NH 234, which Connects Villupuram to Mangalore via Thiruvannamalai Vellore Gudiyatham.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - The town has a lot of buses frequently to major cities and also serves the frequent bus services to nearby towns. Viluppuram is also the headquarters of the Tamil Nadu State Transport Corporation Viluppuram Division. Viluppuram Bus Station is one of the largest bus terminuses by area in Tamil Nadu.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - BHUVANA RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT 293/3, TIRUCHI CHENNAI HIGHWAY, VASHUDHAN NAGAR, VALUDUREDDI - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;PARATHO, CHAPPATHI AND DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - VILLUPURAM,TAMIL NADU, THALAPAKATTU &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT CHIDAMBARAM STREET, CHAIRMAN CHIDAM, K K NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR BIRYANI WITH FRIED EGG)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - MADHAVAN MESS MANDHAKARAI, LOCATED AT FATHIMA LAYOUT - (FAMOUS FOR PAROTTA, PLAIN DOSA AND PUDHINA CHUTNEY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - RAMALINGAM TEA STALL, LOCATED AT THIRU VI KA STREET - {FAMOUS FOR BONDA IS A SNACK MADE FROM GRAM FLOUR BATTER, POTATO (OR OTHER VEGETABLES)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - LALAJI, LOCATED AT FATHIMA LAYOUT, KAMARAJAR STREET, MANDAKKARAI - (FAMOUS FOR PANI PURI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - VINOTH, LOCATED AT 38, K.K. ROAD, MANI NAGAR, CHAIRMAN CHIDAM, SALAMEDU - {FAMOUS FOR KAALAN IS A DISH MADE FROM YOGURT, COCONUT AND VEGETABLE LIKE NENDRAN PLANTAIN OR YAM), CHICKEN MASALA PURI}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - CAKE PLAZA, LOCATED AT OPPOSITE TO COURT BUILDINGS NEAR NEW BUS STAND, TRICHY TRUNK ROAD, K K NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR VARITIES OF CAKES)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(532, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'AMARKANTAK (ANUPPUR)', 'GM.jpg', 'GM1.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The glorious district in the Madhya Pradesh is Anuppur. The Anuppur is mainly known in all over the world for the udgam of holy river Narmada. The beautiful temples present in the Anuppur are mind blowing. Anuppur district is situated in the north eastern part of Madhya Pradesh. This district was formed on 15th August 2003 by re-organizing Shahdol district. This district has a lot of place for the tourism and is visited by the lot of tourists every year. The best tourism place in Anuppur is Amarkantak. The town of Amarkantak lies in the newly created district of Anuppur, in Madhya Pradesh. It is situated on the Maikal mountain range which links the Vindhyachal and Satpura mountain ranges, at about 1067 mts above mean sea level. Amarkantak is a pilgrim town and a nagar panchayat in Anuppur District in the state of Madhya Pradesh, India. Also called Teerthraj the king of pilgrimages, Amarkantak region is a unique natural heritage area and is the meeting point of the Vindhyas and the Satpuras, with the Maikal Hills being the fulcrum. This is where the Narmada River, the Son River and Johila River emerge. Amarkantak situated on the western edge of ancient Kingdom of Kalinga is a place of worship for all the three worlds. Gods and Gandharvas, Asuras, Saints and Sages have all achieved great spiritual powers here. It is believed that whoever dies at Amarkantak is assured of a place in heaven. Also if a lady makes offerings of fruits and flowers will gain the respect of her husband, and no doubt she will also achieve a place in heaven.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Amarkantak is an important tourist attraction in the state of Madhya Pradesh and to suffice to its standards, a large range of hotels right from luxury to budge hotel are available in Amarkantak.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Jabalpur Airport is the nearest airport to Amarkantak that is located at a distance of 245 kms. Taxis are easily available from the airport up to Amarkantak.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - There are state run buses from Pendra Road, Shahdol and Bilaspur to Amarkantak. The city is very well connected to all the major cities of the country hence it wouldn&#39;t be an issue.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The nearest railway station to Amarkantak is Pendra Road at a distance of 17 kms from the heart of the city. Anuppur at distance of 48 kms from Amarkantak is also convenient for the tourists.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Given the fact that Amarkantak is a very small town, most of the intra city travel is done by foot. Another alternative for this matter can be through auto rickshaws. Taxis are also available but they are not as frequently visible as the auto rickshaws.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(533, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'ASHOKNAGAR', 'india-771288_12802.jpg', 'india-771288_12803.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><br />\r\nAshoknagar is famous for the Jain temple called Trikaal Choubeese, where the idols of past, present, and future Thirthankars, as described in the Jain religion, have been kept. The district is also famous for a small town called Chanderi, which is about 60 kms from Ashoknagar. In Chanderi, ancient sculptures have been discovered in large numbers. Thubonji Sidhdha Kshetra is another one of the pilgrim centre for Jains. It is about 32 kms from Ashoknagar. In the south, about 35 kms from Ashoknagar, is the famous Karila Mata Mandir, which is known to be the birthplace of Luv and Kush, sons of Lord Rama and Sita Mata. A huge fair is organized every year on Rangpanchmi in which Rai Dance is performed by Bedni Women. Tumen is also a famous historical pilgrim centre situated at Triveni known for Mata Vindhyavasini temple. There are many more places of religious importance in the district of Ashoknagar. Chanderi is a tehsil of Ashoknagar district and is a famous historical &amp; tourist palace. The main occupation of the people of Chanderi is handicraft. Chanderi saris are famous all over the world. These are made by cotton and silk by hand through Khatka. Khatka is a self made machine for preparing saris. Another famous place in Ashoknagar district is Sri Anandpur, the world headquarters of Sri Advaith Paramhansa Sect. Disciples from across the globe visit Anandpur twice a year during Baisakhi and Guru Purnima to seek blessings from the gurus. Kadwaya, a small village in the district is also famous for the ancient Shiva Mandir, Garhi and Mata Mandir.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">The rest house is available for the tourists who come here from the far flung area. They get a warm welcome with free Lunch/Dinner.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - There are no regular flights from other major cities of the country to Ashoknagar. Nearest airport is Bhopal Airport 147 kms from Ashoknagar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - Ashoknagar is well connected to other major cities of the country via regular trains.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Instead of Ashoknagar tourists can a get a bus to Guna on regular basis.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(534, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'BALAGHAT', 'tiger-959868_640.jpg', 'tiger-959868_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">District Balaghat looks like a flying bird and is situated in southern part of Jabalpur division. &nbsp;It occupies the south eastern region of the Satpura and Upper Wainganga Valley. The total area of the district is 9245 sq kms. District Balaghat is bounded by Rajnandgaon in the East, Seoni in the West, District Mandla in the North and District Bhandara of Maharashtra State in the south. The Wainganga River separates the district from Seoni while the rivers Bawanthadi and Bagh define the inter-state boundary. Balaghat district was constituted during the years 1967-73 by amalgamation of parts of the Bhandara, Mandla and Seoni districts. The headquarter of the district was originally called Burha or Boora later, this name fell into disuse and was replaced by Balaghat, which was originally the name of the district only. The Wainganga is the most important river of the district. Balaghat is the administrative district headquarters. The district of Balaghat has varied geographical conditions across that include low lands, valleys and plateaus. The forests have rich flora and fauna. Teak, Sal, Bamboo and Saja are the main trees in the forest and the wildlife is extensive with a part of the Kanha National Park cutting into the city limits of Balaghat. &nbsp;The biodiversity of these forests is amazing with Tigers, Leopard, Bear, Neel Gai and Deer and Bison sharing the other half of the forest with the avifauna including Peacock, Red Bulbul and Koyal. The name Balaghat suggests the meaning as above the ghats.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">After reaching Balaghat, tourists will be able to get many hotels, resorts and residencies to reside in. And they can choose any of these to stay comfortable and walk around the nearest attractions in and around Balaghat. Travellers will find 5-star, 4-star, 3-star and other luxury and budget hotels, meant for families, individuals as well as for business trip at Balaghat.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Sonegaon airport at Nagpur about 121 kms and Jabalpur airport at Jabalpur about 134 kms are the two airports located near to Balaghat. One can also avail the services of local/state owned (MPSRTC) buses for Balaghat.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Balaghat is situated on narrow gauge line of Jabalpur Balaghat and broad gauge line of Balaghat Gondia section of south eastern railway. Therefore the nearest broad gauge railway station is Gondia, Maharashtra which is at a distance of about 4.6 kms from Balaghat.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Balaghat is well connected by road. State Highways 11 and 26 are the nearest connecting highways to the city of Balaghat.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - The city of Balaghat is directly linked with important places such as Bhopal, Nagpur, Gondia, Jabalpur, Raipur etc by state owned (MPSRTC) bus services. Therefore one can drive down or avail the services of local and Government bus services to move to Balaghat from the above mentioned nearby and major cities of the states, namely Maharashtra and Madhya Pradesh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Tourists can find local taxis, buses, cars and other luxurious and non luxurious vehicles in Balaghat. If comfortable with the railways, then one can move to the city through the trains as well. Though Balaghat is a small place, tourists will be able to get many vehicles for travel comfort.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - MAHAKAL CHAT GUPCHUP CENTRE, LOCATED IN BALAGHAT - {FAMOUS FOR CHAT ITEMS (SNACKS)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - BALAGHAT - {FAMOUS FOR ACHAR GOSHT IS A MEAT DISH PREPARED FROM CHICKEN AND COOKED IN PICKLE SPICES}</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(535, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'BARWANI', 'street-249925_640.jpg', 'street-249925_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">District Barwani was formed on 25th May 1998. It was carved out of west Nimar, Khargone district. Barwani is situated on the south west side of Madhya Pradesh as well as Holy River Narmada is its northern border. District is surrounded by Satpuda and Vindhyachal forest ranges. The name Badwani originated from the forests of Bad which had surrounded the city in old times. Wani is the old word for the Garden and hence city got its name Badwani which means Garden of Bads. Barwani is still pronounced as Badwani but it spells Barwani. Town Barwani was the capital of old Barwani State before 1948. This small State was spared by British, Mughals and Marathas because of its rocky terrain and less productive soil. The Rana dynasty ruled the state through the history. The history of this dynasty goes back to 13th century. State of Maharashtra in South, Gujarat in far west, district Khargone on the east and district Dhar on the north from boundaries of Barwani. District is triangular in shape with the highest point in west. The town Barwani is situated near the left bank of the Narmada River. Town Barwani was also known as Badnagar and Siddha Nagar. The place is also famous for Chool Giri, Jain pilgrimage centre of Bawangaja. Barwani has a historic symbol which is known as Tir Gola. It is located at Khandwa Baroda road, in front of Sagar Vilas Palace and was built in the memory of late son of Raja Ranjit Singh.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Barwani has some deluxe and many medium to budget accommodation options.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport is Devi Ahilyabai Holkar Airport Indore, which is 150 kms from Barwani, provides connectivity to Mumbai, Delhi, Ahmedabad, Hyderabad, Kolkata, Bangalore, Pune, Raipur and Nagpur in India with major airlines operating on these routes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Barwani has Western Railway Reservation Counter (Ratlam Mandal) at Ambedker Park on Rajghat Road. The nearest railway station is situated at Indore, which is one of the major commercial railway stations of western railway. Another nearer railway station is Khandwa, which is 180 km from Barwani.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Barwani is fairly well connected to other parts of Madhya Pradesh and India with national and state highways. The city is connected to the Agra Bombay NH 03 by Khandwa Baroda SH 26 at the distance of 45 kms at Julwaniya. There are bus services to and from all major and minor cities near Barwani.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - JAMBU HOTEL, LOCATED IN BARWANI - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORI AND JALEBI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - PRASHANT HOTEL, LOCATED IN BARWANI&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;- (FAMOUS FOR POHA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - BHARAKADEVI, LOCATED IN BARWANI - (FAMOUS FOR ICE-CREAM)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(536, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'BHIND', 'BA5.jpg', 'BA6.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Bhind the land of Bibhandak Rishi is geographically known for its Ravines, Fertile land and dense Forests. Bhind was one among the 16 districts of United State of Madhya Bharat which was constituted on 28th May 1948. Subsequently, as a result of reorganization of States in November 1956, district Bhind became part of new Madhya Pradesh. Formerly there were 4 Tehsils viz; Bhind, Mehgoan, Gohad and Lahar but at Present there are 7 Tehsils viz; Bhind, Ater, Mehgaon, Gohad, Mihona, Lahar and Raun. As per the History, the district is named after the Bhindi Rishi. It is well known fact that the region has been subjected to depredations of dacoits, robbers or thugs since ages. The majestic Chambal surrounded yawning chasms and gaping beehads provide an ideal setting to this murky banditry in a big way. Even during Mughal times the powerful administration failed to curb these menace. As many as 216 dacoits were shot dead and 697 arrested in Bhind district alone from 1959 to 1963. With an area of 4459 sq kms, the district ranks 20th in population ranking in the State having about 2 percent of the state&#39;s population. The sex ratio of the district according to 2001 census is 829. Rural sex ratio is 825 and Urban is 843. The sex ratio is the number of females per 1000 males. The soil of Bhind is very fertile and is well drained by the Chambal and Sind rivers and the tributary streams of the Kunwari and Puhuj.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">One can choose from a number of accommodation options available in Bhind. From mid size, luxury to budget hotels available in the city one can choose as per the requirements depending upon the individual&rsquo;s needs, budget and location preference. The hotels in Bhind offer prompt &amp; efficient service along with all basic amenities promising you a safe, comfortable &amp; pleasant stay.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest Airport is Gwalior Airport, situated at a distance of 64 kms from the place and is well connected with the cities like Indore, Bhopal, Delhi, Agra, Mumbai, Jaipur and Varanasi etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - Bhind has its own railhead named as Bhind railway station and it is well connected to major cities like Delhi, Chandigarh, Ganganagar, Dehradun, Allahabad, Jammu and Meerut etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - A network of roads &amp; highways including Etawah Gwalior State Highway connect Bhind with surrounding places and to cities across India. Easily available modes of transport are available to travel across the city like State &amp; private run buses, taxis, private vehicles, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport </strong>- A number of auto rickshaws, buses and cycle rickshaws also ply in the city for local transportation &amp; sightseeing. In Bhind the auto rickshaws do not run on meter but one can negotiate for the amount. Though a little expensive option, Auto-rickshaws &amp; Taxis provides a safer &amp; comfortable mode of transport and can be availed during times of urgency. One can easily book a taxi for whole day sightseeing with family &amp; friends. To go to nearby places one can take a cycle rickshaw which is the most convenient option available.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(537, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'BURHANPUR', 'romance-1656549_6401.jpg', 'romance-1656549_6402.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Burhanpur is a district in the Indian state of the Madhya Pradesh. It is a historical town on the north bank of the Tapti River. Burhanpur town was established in Mughal era, around 1400 AD by King Nasir Khan Farukhi. Burhanpur is also known as the Gateway of South. It is also called the dakkan ka darwaza. Burhanpur district has the lot of places to visit. The district consists of religious as well historical places to visit in the city. Due to all such panoramic features of this city attracts a lot of the peoples from all over the region to visit this iconic district. Burhanpur is a historical town based on the banks of the Tapti River in Madhya Pradesh. The most interesting piece of trivia would be that Mumtaz Begum, the reason why the Taj Mahal was built, died in Burhanpur while giving birth to her fourteenth child. The Queen who immortalized love was buried here for the next 23 years waiting the completion of her famed tomb in Agra. It is located in south west of Madhya Pradesh state in Central India. This town has a lot of history to it. Burhanpur is also blessed with an amazing water supply system that was developed during the Mughal rule. All in all, a must visit place for tourists who love discovering about our past. The place has many monuments of historic art &amp; architectural importance like Biwi ki Masjid, Jami Masjid, Badshahi quila, Tombs of Nasir Khan &amp; Adil Shah, Raja ki Chhatri, Khooni Bhandar. The place is also counted in the pilgrimage of Sikhkha sect. The handloom industry of the city has a remarkable place in the household industries and has a glorious past.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Burhanpur is an important tourist attraction in the state of Madhya Pradesh and to ensure that MP does not lose out on any of the tourism, it will very well observed that Burhanpur has a lot of accommodation facilities. Right from state run accommodation lodges to budget hotels, tourists will find enough options to suffice their accommodation needs.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Burhanpur does not have an aerodrome of its own. The Indore Airport is in the closest proximity to the city of Burhanpur which is 163 kms away.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Burhanpur is well connected to the major towns of India very roadways. One can easily get regular buses to Burhanpur from other major cities of the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Burhanpur is well connected to other major cities of the country via regular trains. The other major railway station close to it is that of Indore.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - A lot of options are available for intra city travel in the city of Burhanpur, but the most feasible option seems to be that of share auto rickshaws. Another option is that of cabs. Buses can also be considered for exploring this marvellous city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - KUNDAN SWEETS, LOCATED AT OLD NAGAR NIGAM RD, MONIN PURA - (FAMOUS FOR MASALA DOSA &nbsp;AND DAHI VADA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - KAMAL, LOCATED AT GANDHI CHOWK, GOTI MAHOLLA - {FAMOUS FOR LASSI (BUTTERMILK)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - KISHOR GARDEN RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT STATE BANK COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR CHILLY PANEER, KAJU CURRY AND CHANNA ROAST)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - DHABA CAFE, LOCATED AT BALAJI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR WADA PAV AND COFFEE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - BURHANPUR JALEBI CENTER, LOCATED AT MONIN PURA - (FAMOUS FOR JALEBI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - MADEENA SWEETS &amp; PISTA BAKERY HOUSE, LOCATED AT PATIDAR COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR MAVA JALEBI)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(538, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'CHHATARPUR', 'zinnia-1646445_1280.jpg', 'zinnia-1646445_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Another feather in the hat of Madhya Pradesh, Chhatarpur is a beautiful historical town. The place is famed for its heritage tourist sites. It can be a perfect place for those seeking both peace and beauty. The natural charm shall offer peace of mind whereas the historical sites will render the opportunity to learn more about the cultural richness of Madhya Pradesh. Chhatarpur seems ideal as a holiday destination for all. The district Chhatarpur was known after the name of the great warrior of the region Maharaja Chhatrasa. This district was previously under the then Vindhya Pradesh. However at the time of formation of the Madhya Pradesh, it was included in Madhya Pradesh on 1st November 1956. A very beautiful and picturesque destination in the state of Madhya Pradesh, Chhatarpur, is an ancient and commercial town in Chhatarpur district of the state. It is also the administrative headquarters of the district. The district is listed as one of the famous places for India&#39;s tourism because of its cultural heritage. Chhatarpur travel guide is full of references to the serene spots and places with immense historical heritage. In the year 1785, the wonderful district was founded and was named after the Bundela Rajput leader Chhatrasal, the promoter of Bundelkhand freedom. The state was ruled by his offspring during 1785. Chhatarpur is one of the oldest cities of Madhya Pradesh, having been founded in 1785. It was named after Chhatrasal, a famous Rajput leader. The district is situated at north east border of Madhya Pradesh. This district is spread over an area of 8687 sq kms.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are plenty of staying options available in this place in which tourists can choose according to the budget and convenience. The hotels in Chhatarpur offer a home staying experience by presenting lots of contemporary features within their elegant rooms. Besides the accommodation, the dining and conferencing services are also provided to the guests.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest Domestic Airport is Khajuraho Airport, roughly 45 minutes drive from Chhatarpur. It is well connected to a spectrum of cities like Varanasi, Delhi and Agra. The nearest International Airport is Bhopal Airport, roughly six hour drive from Chhatarpur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- The nearest Railway Station is Khajuraho Railway Station which is connected to the major cities of Madhya Pradesh. It is well connected to the cities such as Delhi, Gwalior, Agra, Mathura, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - The city of Chhatarpur is well connected to the major cities of Madhya Pradesh via road. There are frequent state transportation bus services running from this city while some private bus operators are also providing their services.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - KANHA VEG RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT OPPOSITE ICICI BANK, JAWAHAR ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR DOASA &nbsp;AND IDILI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - SKY LARK, LOCATED AT NAYA MOHALLA - (FAMOUS FOR SOUTH INDIAN FOOD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - SAHU SWEETS BUS STAND, LOCATED AT VISHWANATH COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - PANCHWATI RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT BRIJPURA, CHHATARPUR, NH-75, PANNA KHAJURAHO ROAD - {FAMOUS FOR CHAI(TEA)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - HARI CHAAT BHANDAAR, LOCATED AT NEAR BUS STAND, NATIONAL HIGHWAY 86, NAYA MOHALLA - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;ALOO TIKKI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - KRISHNA GOTIRAM, LOCATED AT CHHATRASAL CHOWK TO SAGAR ROAD, SHANTI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR VARITIES OF SWEETS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(539, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'CHHINDWARA', 'elephant-597391_640.jpg', 'elephant-597391_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Chhindwara, in Madhya Pradesh is one of the big towns in the Satpura range. Located on the plateau, the place has lush green surroundings, with rivers and sagaun trees. The town forms one of the southern districts of Madhya Pradesh. This district is bound by the plains of Nagpur district on the South, Hoshangabad and Narsinghpur districts on the North, Betul district on the West and Seoni districts on the East. Surrounded by dense forest, the place is rich in flora and fauna. Besides, it is considered to be one among the coolest places in Madhya Pradesh during summer season and is visited by many people. A large population of Chhindwara is of tribes, which majority of them speaks Gondi and Hindi mixed with Marathi. A peaceful town with rich culture, Chhindwara has a lot of tourist places. Some of the attractions that can be visited include Patalkot, Tamia, Tribal Museum, Chota Mahadev Cave, Devgarh Fort and many more. In fact, the place is home of many well known temples and mosques. Many cultural functions and festivals are celebrated in Chhindwara district. Some of the most popular festivals are Pola, Bhujalia, Meghnath and Akhadi.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">To make the stay in Chhindwara comfortable and convenient, the city has number of budget hotels with amusing ambiance and world class facilities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Chhindwara does not have an airport, and the nearest airport is Sonegaon Airport in Jabalpur, at a distance of 65 kms from Chhindwara. Jabalpur is connected to other Indian cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Chhindwara does not have a train station, and the nearest station is Jabalpur, at a distance of 52 kms from Chhindwara. Jabalpur has two train stations. They are Jabalpur and Howbadh Jabalpur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Frequent buses and taxi services keep connected nearby big cities like Bhopal, Nagpur, and Jabalpur. It is connected by National Highway 69.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - TANEJA BAKERY, LOCATED AT KHAJRI ROAD, SINCHAI COLONY, MOHAN NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR PARATHA, CAKES, SANDWICHES AND BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - NASHTEWALA, LOCATED AT OPPOSITE RAILWAY STATION, SEONI ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR SOUTH INDIAN FOOD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - 8 BN, LOCATED AT RING ROAD, HOUSING BOARD COLONY, SINCHAI COLONY, MOHAN NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR JALEBI, AALU WADA AND SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - RAJPUROHIT SWEETS, LOCATED AT 1, CHHINDWARA RD, BARARIPURA, RAUTHA WADA - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n5 - CHHINDWARA - {FAMOUS FOR KHTTA CHIWDA &nbsp;IS A &nbsp;SNACK MADE FROM RICE (FRIED &nbsp;IN OIL) AND THEN SPICES, PEANUTS, SOMETIMES RAISINS AND TURMERIC POWDER AND &nbsp;SERVED WITH TEA OR COFFEE}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(540, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'DAMOH', 'lotus-1782638_1280.jpg', 'lotus-1782638_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The district has many places of historical importance. The town of Nohata is one such example and is situated at a distance of 21 kms from Damoh, on the banks of River Gauraya and was a capital of the Chandela Rajputs. There are a number of temples there. The ancient fort at Rajnagar village, 6 kms from Damoh, was founded by the Mughals. Singhorgarh fort is another place of historical importance. It was built by Raja Vain Bason. Gond Rajas stayed in it for a long time. It was with Gond Raja Dalpat Shah and his Rani Durgawati at the end of 15th century. After the death of Raja Dalpat Shah, the Senapati of the army of Mughal emperor Akbar had a battle with Rani Durgawati at village Singrampur. The town of Narsinghgarh, situated on Sonar River, has an ancient fort built by Shah Taiyab. Birla group has established a cement factory at Narsinghgarh. Kundalpur is famous place for Jain temples. Situated 32 kms from Damoh, there are 58 Jain temples in Kundalpur. Jageshwarnath temple at Bandakpur is a famous Hindu pulgrimage center. In damoh district the Lodhi Rajput and Rai are more power full. Damoh city has a beautiful Ghantaghar, circuit house and statue of Maharana Pratap at Jabalpur Naka, Kirti Stambh, Gajanan pahadi, Naugaja pahadi and fort of Rani Damyanti Bai near tehsil ground, Nehru Park and a very beautiful Jatashankar temple.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">For accommodation, one can find all types of hotels in Damoh that is from affordable family hotels to the most luxurious ones. Luxury hotels offer facilities such as 24 hour room service, multi-cuisine restaurants, doctors on call etc.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Nearest airport to Damoh is at Jabalpur, situated at a distance of about 95 kms and from there it takes around 1 to 2 hours to reach Damoh. Jabalpur airport is well connected to major cities of the country such as Delhi, Mumbai etc. The nearest International airport to Damoh is Bhopal about 265 kms.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Damoh is the only railway station in the city that serves well for major cities like Delhi, Mumbai and Howrah. This rail head is managed by Western Central Railways.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Damoh is well connected by motor able roads with the major regions of Madhya Pradesh state. State Highways 14, 37 and 49 are the nearest connecting highways to the city of Damoh.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Damoh Bus Station is very near to the Damoh Railway Station, hardly few minute walk. Both Local and Madhya Pradesh State Road Transport Corporation operates regular buses connecting to all major cities in the state such as Jabalpur, Nagpur, Allahabad, Raipur, Bhopal and Sagar.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - MANGALAM RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT MP SH 37, INDUSTRIAL AREA - (FAMOUS FOR DAAL FRY AND BUTTER CHAPATI)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(541, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'DATIA', 'landscape-629809_640.jpg', 'landscape-629809_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Datia is the district headquarters of the Datia district. It is an ancient town, mentioned in the Mahabharata as Daityavakra. The town is a market centre for food grains and cotton products. Handloom weaving is an important industry. Datia is a famed for the seven storied palace built by Raja Beer Singh Deo in 1614. A pilgrimage spot for devotees, Datia has the sidhapeeth of shri peetambhara Devi, Buglamukhi Devi Temple and Gopeshwar temple. About 15 Km from Datia is the Sonagiri, a scared Jain hill. Peetambra peeth is a famous shaktipitha located at the entrance of Datia in Madhya Pradesh. This pilgrimage spot features Buglamukhi Devi Temple and Dhumavati Mai Temple established by Shri Golokwasi Swamiji Maharaj. Vankhandeshwar temple is a Mahabharata period temple of Lord Shiva which is situated at this place. Datia had formerly been a state in the Bundelkhand region. The ruling family were Rajputs of the Bundela clan; they descended from a younger son of a former raja of Orchha. The state was administered as part of the Bundelkhand agency of Central India. It lay in the extreme north west of Bundelkhand, near Gwalior, and was surrounded on all sides by other princely states of Central India, except on the east where it bordered upon the United Provinces. It was second highest in the rank of all the Bundela states after Orchha, with a 15 gun salute, and its Maharajas bore the hereditary title of Second of the Princes of Bundelkhand.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Datia is home to many hotels and lodges. Also, tourists can stay in numerous ashrams and dharmashalas. However, for a tourist looking for a luxurious stay may want to stay either in Jhansi, about 25 kms from Datia or Gwalior, which is 69 kms from Datia.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Datia is well connected by road. Tourists can take the NH 75 which, after Datia also stretches towards Jhansi, which lies at about 27 kms from Datia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - Datia has its own railway station which is located on the Delhi Chennai main line.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Air</strong> - Gwalior airport which is about 70 kms from the city is the nearest airport.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - MAHALAXMI SNACKS AND SWEETS, LOCATED IN DATIA - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(542, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'DEWAS', 'holiday-661959_1280.jpg', 'holiday-661959_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">A very attractive and exquisite destination, Dewas located in the state of Madhya Pradesh is an ancient town in the administrative centre of the Dewas district. It is situated on the Malwa plateau in the west central part of India and is 160 kms from state capital, Bhopal. The name of the city Dewas means the Abode of Gods. Dewas is often visited by locals of the state as well as by the tourists from all over the country in pursuit of serenity. The name of the town Dewas is derived from the Devi Vaishini hill in the town, also known as Tekri. The hill has a big temple of Goddess Devi Chamunda Tulja Bhavani and Kalika Mata which captivates large number of tourists from all over India. Dewas is also a major industrial town and houses many giant market players like Ranbaxy Labs, Tata, Gabriel India Ltd. and Kirloskars etc. During the British period, Dewas was the seat of two 15 Gun Salute royal states i.e. Dewas Junior state and Dewas Senior state, ruled by the Maratha clan Puar. Two theories prevail about the name of the city, one being that Dewas lies on the foot of Chamunda hill on top of which is the shrine of Goddess Chamunda, from which the name is derived Dewas meaning Devi Vashini or the Goddess residence. The other theory is that maybe the name was given as a mark of respect to the founder of the village Dewasa Bania. Dewas is a fast developing industrial town with the government&rsquo;s bank note press located in the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Finding a suitable accommodation will not be a problem if are planning a trip to the holy city of Dewas with a number of Hotels and Guest houses present in the city. One can choose the hotels as per their budget &amp; accommodation requirements, though it is always advised to opt for a reputed hotel. While going for sightseeing one can take directions from the courteous and always ready to help hotel staff.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest International Airport from Dewas is Devi Ahilyabai Holkar Airport, Indore, roughly half an hour drive from the city. It is well connected to a spectrum of cities like Varanasi, Delhi, Lucknow, Kathmandu, Bhopal, Hyderabad and Kolkata etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Dewas Junction (DWX), is a part of Ratlam division of western India Railways and is an important railway station with many trains plying to &amp; fro from the city.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Situated on the National Highway 3 on Agra Mumbai Road, Dewas has an extensive network of National and state highways like NH 86 and Dewas Bhopal Corridor which connect the city to other major cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- One can choose from the different modes of local transportation like Buses, taxis, cycle rickshaws and autos as per as their convenience.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - APNA SWEETS, LOCATED AT AB ROAD, SHIVAJI NAGAR, GOMTI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR GUJIYA AND MOONG DAL FRY LADDOO)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - ANYTIME FAST FOOD AND BAKERY, LOCATED AT 85, AB ROAD, OPPOSITE BUS STAND, TEKRI AREA, GOMTI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR CAKES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - RATAN SHREE, LOCATED AT 71, KALI DAS-E-DEWAS, KAVI KALIDAS MARG - (FAMOUS FOR SHIKANJI AND POHA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - INDORE&#39;S NASTA POINT, LOCATED AT MENDKI ROAD, CIVIL LINES CHOURAHA, GOMTI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - COOL UNCLE ICE CREAM PARLOUR, LOCATED AT 10/A, MUKHERJEE NAGAR, NAGAR NIGAM COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;PIZZA AND BURGER)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - MUKESH SWEETS &amp; RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT AB ROAD, MOTI BUNGLOW CHOURAHA, SHIVAJI NAGAR, GOMTI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA AND KACHORI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - CHAPAN BHOG, LOCATED AT AB ROAD, SET MISHRILAL NAGAR, GANGA NAGAR - {FAMOUS FOR LASSI (BUTTERMILK)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - ANAND SWEETS, LOCATED AT AB ROAD, OPPOSITE LNB COLONY, ANAND BAGH, TARANI COLONY, PACHUNKAR COLONY, GOMTI NAGAR - {FAMOUS FOR SWEETS ARE ( MAWABATI AND MALAI BARFI) AND SEW IS A SNACK}</strong></p>\r\n', '');
