(543, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'DHAR', 'india-380051_6402.jpg', 'india-380051_6403.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Dhar is a place of cultural and historical appeal of the destinations of Madhya Pradesh. Located in the Malwas region of Madhya Pradesh Dhar has its own significance as one of the most culturally rich destinations of Madhya Pradesh. Ruled by the Puaras, this place was a Maratha princely state and acquired the status of a Salute State, a sheer royalty during that period. There are many tourist places in and around Dhar. The Bagh Caves is a must visit. Another famous attraction is Pithampur, which is an industrial town. Dhar is the small town situated in the western region of Madhya Pradesh. The location of Dhar is extremely relevant and adds to the picturesque beauty of the place. Situated at 559 mts above sea level, Dhar is surrounded by lakes and hills and also old buildings containing immense historical importance, making Dhar tourism distinct. Fine arts, paintings, sculpture, music and dance form an integral part of Dhar. The people of Dhar from time immemorial have been thoroughly engaged in the work pertaining to arts and made their presence felt all over the world. The painting in the famous Bagh Caves speaks highly about the rich cultural potential of the people during the Gupta Period. The famous love story of Baaz Bahadur and Roopmati has inspired generations and still continues to do so. Every corner of this town speaks about their love story. Be it literature, dance or music, Baaz Bahadur himself took interest in cultivating these art forms and attained considerable recognition making Dhar well known. Dhar can be best visited during the months of October and November.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There aren&rsquo;t many hotels in Dhar. One has to choose from guest houses and budget hotels available for accommodation.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\n<strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest airport to Dhar is the Devi Ahilyabai Holkar National Airport in Indore which is at a distance of 62 kms. The Airport is connected to major cities of India.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Dhar does not have a rail head. One can either get down at Indore which is 62 kms which is connected to major cities. Alternatively, Ratlam which is 93 kms has four major Railway Tracks passing which are along Mumbai, Delhi and Ajmer.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Dhar is well connected by road to major cities within the state of Madhya Pradesh. National Highway 59 links Ahmedabad in Gujarat with Indore in Madhya Pradesh passes through Dhar. The National Highway 79 connects Ajmer in Rajasthan and Dhar in Madhya Pradesh.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Dhar is connected by bus to prominent towns in Madhya Pradesh. One can avail the services of local and Government operated MPSRTC bus services travel to and from Dhar town.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SHRI RAM VIJAY TEA HOUSE, &nbsp;LOCATED AT EKATA CHOUPATTY, NEAR MOHAN TALKIES - (&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;FAMOUS FOR POHA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - YADAV, &nbsp;LOCATED AT LIG COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR PAAN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - MAA KAUSHIKI RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT MHOW-GHATABILLOD ROAD, NEAR INDORAMA MANDIR - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - MATESHWARI, LOCATED IN DHAR&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; - (FAMOUS FOR POHA AND JALEBI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - KRISHNA PALACE, LOCATED IN DHAR - (FAMOUS FOR DAL BATTI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - JIJA, LOCATED AT 63 M G ROAD, DHAR NAKA MHOW - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - SANDEEP RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT DHAR ROAD, GANGWAY BUS STAND - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA AND TEA)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(544, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'DINDORI', 'fly-637946_1280.jpg', 'fly-637946_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><br />\r\nDindori district is situated at the eastern part of Madhaya Pradesh touching Chhattisgarh state. It touches Shahdol in east, Mandla in west, Umaria in north, and Bilaspur district of Chhattisgarh State in south. The holy river Narmada passes through the district. It is situated at a height of 1100 mts above sea level amongst herbal rich, Maikal mountain ranges. Dindori has many historical as well as spiritual places. Some of the spiritual places are Laxman Madva, Kukarramath and Kalchuri Kali Mandir etc. The Kanha Tiger National Park is 180 kms and Bandhavgarh National Park is 140 kms away from the district headquarter. It was created on 25th May, 1998 with total 927 villages. The district is covered in seven blocks namely Dindori, Shahpura, Mehandwani, Amarpur, Bajag, Karanjiya &amp; Samnapur. The Baiga are very Particularly Vulnerable Tribal Groups which can be found only in this district. The Baigas are known as the National Human. Dindori has a moderate climate and evenings are pleasant. Undulated lands, mountains, valleys, river streams and thick forest cover give the entire District a serene look, which attracts many nature lovers and is becoming a famous eco-tourism destination.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">There are several medium budget hotels, lodges and govt. guest houses available in the city for accommodation of tourists, with basic facilities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air </strong>- Nearest Airport to Dindori is Dumna airport, Jabalpur at about 144 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Train </strong>- Nearest Railway station to Dindori is Pendra Road at about 30 kms. Shahdol Railway station is another major railhead near Dindori at a distance of about 90 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Road </strong>- Nearest Bus stand to Dindori is Dindori Bus stand. Regular buses ply to and from Dindori to various nearby cities. It has good connectivity from Jabalpur, Mandla, Bilaspur and Shahdol.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(545, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'GUNA', 'animal-1868911_640.jpg', 'animal-1868911_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Guna gateway of Malwa &amp; Chambal is located on the north eastern part of Malwa Platue between Parbati and the Betwa. The western boundary of the district is well defined by the river. The Parbati is the main river flowing along the western boundary touching Rajgarh district of MP and Jhalawarh and Kota district of Rajasthan. Shivpuri and Kota are located in north where as Vidisha, Bhopal, and Rajgarh lies to the South. Initially Guna sees to be the part of Avanti Kingdom founded by Chand Pradyota Mahesena Later on Shishusangh added the kingdom of Avant which included Guna to the growing empire of Magadha. In the beginning of 18th century Chanderi was the part of Malwa and remaining portion of Guna formed the part of Raghogarh State. Later on Raghogarh was split into three state of which Garah and Dharnawada State among the three claimants of Raghogarh family. After the great revolt of 1857, Guna district thus passed under the control of Gwalior State with Raghogarh as its mandatory chief. An assistant to the resident of Gwalior was posted at Guna, which remained an English cantonment after the year 1860. Although Guna was dejure a part of Gwalior State, but because of its British cantonment, it was considered expedient to locate the district headquarter there. Bajrangarh, about 6 miles from Guna enjoyed that privilege. In 1897 the midland railway constructed the rail route passing through Guna. After independence on 28th May 1948, Guna became the part of Madhya Bharat as one of its 16 districts subsequently as a result of State on the formation of new Madhya Pradesh in 1956 Guna district became a part of it.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Though there are a few luxury hotels available in this part of Madhya Pradesh yet they are equipped with basic facilities and ensure cool and conformable stay of their guests. Tourists can choose the hotels based on their tariffs, luxuries and comforts offered. Guna has different types of hotels available for families, friends, kids, lovers and specially designed rooms for honeymooners.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Guna tourism offers excellent flight services. One who wishes to visit Guna via air network has to take a flight and reach the capital of Madhya Pradesh, Bhopal. It is the nearest air destination to Guna. Bhopal is located at a distance of 188 kilometres from Guna.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - It is on the broad gauge railway line where the Guna railway station is located. One has to visit the nearest station Pathankot in order to travel to the major cities of the country. The transportation to Guna is very fast, and in the recent years particular care has been taken by the Government of Madhya Pradesh to make the process better and faster.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Guna is situated on the Agra Mumbai National Highway 3 well connected with different parts of the district of Guna as well as with different states of Madhya Pradesh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - There are a number of private buses and government buses plying to the city of Guna. The comforts level of the buses varies depending upon their fare and services. For those looking for extra comfort it is advisable to board Volvo buses that fitted with air conditioning system.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SHIMLA SWEETS, LOCATED AT JAI STAMBH CHOWK,A.B. ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR MASALA DRINK)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - RIDDHIMA, LOCATED AT LAXMI GANJ - (FAMOUS FOR CHAT ITEMS)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(546, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'ITARSI', 'street-249925_6402.jpg', 'street-249925_6403.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Itarsi, nestled in Hoshangabad district of Madhya Pradesh, is a business hub with a famous railway junction. The city has made its mark due to its strong foothold in the agricultural and industrial sectors. The presence of the oldest and largest railway junction of Madhya Pradesh has added to the commercial development of the city. Itarsi is renowned for its handloom clothing and boasts of a flourishing ancient art and craft industry. It is located at a distance of 90 kms from Bhopal. Itarsi derives its name from the previously prevalent trade of the town in bricks and rope. Today the plywood industry has emerged as the prevailing trade. The mineral rich city of Itarsi has an Ordnance factory that serves the arms requirement of the Indian Armed Forces. The presence of soya oil mills and several other industries has helped to establish the city as a prime commercial centre. Itarsi tourism presents vivid attractions or tourist places that include the Tawa reservoir situated on the Tawa River and Bori Wildlife Sanctuary. The best time to travel to this city is during the winter season.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Accommodation is also not a cause to worry in Itarsi as it has many guest houses and hotels of all categories and one can choose according to ones budget and requirement. Tourists coming to the city can choose from mid budget to high end hotels as per their budget. The Hotels in Itarsi offer quality and courteous services to their guests thus enhancing customer satisfaction and thus repeat business.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport to Itarsi is situated at Bhopal, the Raja Bhoj Airport. It is at a distance of about 111 kms from the commercial city. It is an international airport with numerous flights connecting Bhopal to other cities and countries.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Itarsi has the largest railway junction in Madhya Pradesh. Itarsi has a strong network of trains connecting it to the other parts of the country. Trains are the easiest and the most economical way to reach Itarsi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - A well developed road network like the National Highway 69 connects Itarsi to major cities like Bhopal &amp; Nagpur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Itarsi is connected by buses and taxis to the nearby cities and especially to Bhopal. The Maharashtra State Road Transport Corporation has started luxury buses which take 8 hours to reach Itarsi from Nagpur.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - GAGAN MAGAN, LOCATED AT STATE HIGHWAY 22, CHAYAN COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA &nbsp;AND TEA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - KANCHAN, LOCATED AT SURAJ GANJ - (FAMOUS FOR JALEBI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - NEW RAJHANS FAMILY RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT SURAJ GANJ - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;DAL FRY AND SAHI PANEER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - KISHORE RESTAURANT, &nbsp;LOCATED AT SHOP NO:6, MAIN ROAD, JAI STAMBH CHOWK, NEAR RAILWAY STATION, HOSHANGABAD - (FAMOUS FOR DAHI VADA AND DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(547, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'JHABUA', 'sunset-1225655_640.jpg', 'sunset-1225655_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Jhabua was the capital of a princely state of the British Raj&#39;s Central India, in the Bhopawar agency. Its area, with the dependency of Rutanmal, was approx 4600 sq kms. After India&#39;s independence in 1947, its rulers acceded to India, and Jhabua became part of the newly created Madhya Bharat state, which in 1956 was merged into Madhya Pradesh. Bhabhara which was once part of the Jhabua district, is the place where Chandrasekhar Azad, the great freedom fighter spent his early life when his father Pandit Sitaram Tiwari was serving in the erstwhile estate of Alirajpur. But, when Alirajpur district got separated from Jhabua Bhabhra became the part of Alirajpur district. River Narmada forms the southern boundary of the district. Jhabua is a predominantly adivasi district, and suffers from high rates of illiteracy and poverty. Almost half of the population lives below the poverty line. The Bhil and Bhilala peoples inhabit the interior of the district. The Bhils celebrate Bhagoria, a tribal festival which coincides with holi, with great fervour. The district is highly drought prone and degraded waste lands form the face for Jhabua. The women make lovely ethnic items including bamboo products, doll, bead jewellery and other items that have for long decorated the living rooms all over the country. The men have since ages adorned Teer Kamthi, the bow and arrow, which has been their symbol of chivalry and self defence.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">While city doesn&rsquo;t have any 5 star hotel, but it does boost decent number of 2 star and 3 star hotels where tourists can enjoy quality luxury accommodation at pretty budget rates.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport to Jhabua is Devi Ahilyabai Holkar International Airport, Indore which is 123 kms away from Jhabua city centre.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - The nearest railway station to Jhabua is Meghnanagar railway station which is 17 kms away from Jhabua city centre.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Tourists can easily get regular buses to Jhabua from other major cities of the country.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>ASHOKA, LOCATED AT NATIONAL HIGHWAY 59 - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(548, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'KATNI', 'asia-754905_640.jpg', 'asia-754905_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Katni is a town on the banks of the Katni River in Madhya Pradesh. It is the administrative headquarters of Katni district. It is located in the Mahakoshal Region of Central India. The city is 90 kms away from the divisional headquarters of the region, Jabalpur. It is one of largest railway junctions in India and has the largest rail yard and biggest diesel locomotive shed in India. City has an abundance of Lime and Bauxite. Katni has had the status of town since the beginning of the 20th century. Development work of the town started under British rule. On 28th May 1998 Katni was declared as a district. Katni is conglomeration of culture from three different cultural states viz. Mahakausal, Bundelkhand, and Baghelkhand. There are three different stories which reveals why Katni is called Mudwara. Katni junction is having half circular turn from wagon yard. So people call it Mudwara. Another story is that there was a village call Modwar that has been given as a reward of bravery for cutting heads. A similar story is about the British government used to cut heads of Baggies and Plunderers, and hang them in squares to make people afraid of doing crimes. Located on the banks of Katni River, city of Katni is the administrative headquarters of the district in Madhya Pradesh. It is home to numerous schools, educational institutions and industrial establishments and thus is an important commercial and industrial centre. Known for its vast reserves of limestone and bauxite, it is also called as the city of marble.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">When it comes to accommodation, there are plenty of options for the visitors of Katni in Madhya Pradesh to choose from. From elegant luxury hotels to budget ones, tourists can opt for anything as per the budget and preferences. Equipped with modern amenities and a clean and well maintained ambience, these hotels provide all sorts of assistance in making the stay a comfortable one.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- The Dumna Airport at Jabalpur about 100 kilometres far is the airport nearest to Katni and has regular flights to major Indian cities, by leading airlines.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Katni Junction is the most important railway line in Katni and there are four other railway junctions here New Katni Junction, Murwara Junction, Madhav Nagar and Katni South Junction.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Due to national highway, communication by roadways is easy and convenient. The major North South National Highway 7, called as NH 7, passes through this city. National Highway 78 is another important highway that starts from Katni city and passes through the three major states of Madhya Pradesh, Chhattisgarh and Jharkhand.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Regular buses connect Katni city to other nearby areas at regular intervals. Various private travel agencies also provide reliable bus services to and from Katni.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Taxis and auto rickshaws form the major mode of transport within the city. People also prefer travelling by scooters, cars and other private vehicles. Private cabs, car rentals, luxury coaches and bus services are provided by various private travel agencies and can be hired at nominal rates for local sightseeing as well as for outstation trips.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - KATNI - {FAMOUS FOR BHUTTE KI KEES IS MADE FROM CORN COOKED IN MILK, ALONG WITH SPICES ; CHAKKI KI SHAAK IS PREPARED FROM WHEAT DOUGH AND CURD}<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - SARDAR DA DHABA, LOCATED AT NH 7, MP SH 10, CHANEHATA - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN WINGS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - ANWAR BHAI, LOCATED AT GOLE BAZAR - (FAMOUS FOR BIRYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - JHALLU CHAT WALE, LOCATED AT MP SH 10, GANDHI GANJ - (&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - GOLU RESTURANT, LOCATED AT HOUSING BOARD COLONY, SHANTI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR JALEBI, DOSA &nbsp;AND IDILI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - LAKHAN, LOCATED AT LAKHERA - {FAMOUS FOR FULKI (PANIPURI)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - LASSI CENTER, LOCATED AT GOLE BAZAR - (FAMOUS FOR BUTTERMILK)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(549, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'KHANDWA', 'road-351925_1280.jpg', 'road-351925_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Khandwa is an ancient city, with many places of worship, like many other cities in India. Mostly they are Hindu and Jain temples. During the 12th century AD it was a centre of Jainism. Recent explorations in the tributaries of Narmada have revealed traces of the Paleolithic men in East Nimar district. Omkar Mandhata, a rocky island on the bank of Narmada River, about 47 miles North West of Khandwa, is said to have been conquered by the Haihaya king Mahishmant, who had named the same as Mahishmati. During the rise of Buddhism, the East Nimar region was included in Avanti Kingdom under Chand Pradyota Mahesana, which was later added to the growing empire of Magadha by Shishunaga. From the early 2nd century BC to late 15th century AD, the Nimar Region earlier a part of Khandesh underwent the ruling of many emperors from many dynasties. The Location, easy availability of resources and other socio economic factors are in favour of making the place a very good Industrial region. The place has several ancient kunds, English architecture and religious places.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">A number of budget, economy, mid range and luxury hotels and guest houses are present in Khandwa to make the stay comfortable. One can opt for the same as per the budget and requirement. These hotels and guest houses offer all basic amenities along with quality room service for convenience. It is always advisable to consult the travel advisor or book a room at a registered hotel only keeping the safety aspect in mind.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\n<strong>By Air </strong>- Though Khandwa has an airstrip situated on the Nagchun Road, this airstrip is mostly used for occasional landings of aircraft. No flights are scheduled here. The nearest commercial airport to Khandwa is the Devi Ahilyabai Holkar International Airport which is located in Indore. The distance between Indore and Khandwa is 141 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Khandwa is located on the Main Train Junction. The Khandwa Railway Station has daily rail connections to the important places in Madhya Pradesh such as Bhopal and Indore.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Khandwa can be reached by road through public transportation such as buses and taxis. Regular buses ply to Khandwa from the neighbouring places and the important places of Madhya Pradesh. The best way to come to Khandwa via road is to travel through Indore.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Auto rickshaws, bicycles, buses and cycle rickshaws form the major mode of local transport to travel within the city which is both affordable and easily available.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - RUSH N CRUSH, LOCATED AT IN FRONT OF S.N COLLEGE VALLABH ENTERPRISES, VAIKUNTH NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR CAKE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - GHAR PARIVAR, LOCATED AT BADABUM CHOWK - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;VEG MANCHURIAN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - CHAHALPAHAL RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT KHANDWA - MUNDI STATE HWY, DEENDAYAL PURAM, RAMESHWAR NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA &nbsp;AND KACHORIS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - KHANDWA - {FAMOUS FOR KUSLI IS A SWEET DISH MADE FROM WHEAT FLOUR, ALMOND, SEMOLINA, SUGAR, COCONUTS, CARDAMOM ; LAVANG LATA IS A SWEET DISH MADE FROM WHEAT FLOUR STUFFED WITH A MIXTURE OF DRY FRUITS, COCONUT, RAISINS, CARDAMOM AND CLOVES THEN IT IS FRIED AND DIPPED IN SUGAR SYRUP}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(550, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'MANDSAUR', 'timber-706750_640.jpg', 'timber-706750_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Mandsaur city represents beautiful amalgam of approximately all religions and languages. The city depicts all colours of Indian culture and religion. Mandsaur is the administrative headquarters of Mandsaur District and is part of Ujjain Division. The city is situated on the border of Malwa and Mewar. The most spoken language in the city is Malvi, which is a mixture of both Rajasthani and Hindi. Mandasaur is also famous for beautiful Saris, decorated bangles and also large production of Opium. The slate pencil industry is the main industry of the city. Mandsaur city with its long impressive history is a major city in Madhya Pradesh. Be it ancient periood or nedieval period or modern period Mandasaur has seen every phases of Indian history. The place finds its mention during Mahabharata period. This historical place is famous for its two great monolith pillars recording a victory of Yasodharman king of Malwa, in 528. Also it served as a seat of power during Gurjara Pratihara period. During medieval period and after the decline of Delhi Sultanate the city came to be ruled by Dilawar Khan Ghauri, the governor of the Malwa province. In 1401 Dilawar Khan took the title of Sultan of Malwa in 1401. He was succeeded by his son Hoshang Shah. The city remained a part of the princely state of Gwalior and after independence was made administrative headquarters of Mandsaur district. Mandasaur city got its name when two of the villages Marh and Saur were merged to create the name of the city. The town was known as Dashpur in ancient times. It is also said that the name originated from Mandodri, wife of Ravana. And the ancient name Dashpur was named after her husband Dashanand, the other name of Ravana.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Mandsaur offers many tourist destinations for the tourists especially for the spiritual people. To make their stay memorable and comfortable many hotels have come across the region. Tourists can choose from a wide range of hotels according to the budget. The hotels offer a variety of facilities according to the charges. The hospitality of the hotels is scoring points. The charges are also affordable and never exceed the budget of the customer.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport to Mandsaur is Maharana Pratap Airport, Udaipur. The airport is 209 kms from Mandsaur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Mandsaur comes under Ratlam rail division is situated on Ajmer Akola track. It comes under Western Railways. Many passenger and express train pass through Mandsaur Junction.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Situated on Ajmer Lebad, National Highway 79 as well as Mhow Neemuch, State Highway 31, a four lane roads Mandsaur is easily connected to all the cities through these highways. The Mandsaur State Highway 14 Bus Station is the focal point for interchange and is operated by the authorities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Mandsaur has a good network of buses. There are frequent bus services from Mandsaur to different parts of the state. The buses connect Mandsaur to all the important cities of Madhya Pradesh. The public buses are looked after by Madhya Pradesh State Road Development Corporation. Tourists can avail various types of buses like Non A/c, A/c and Ashok Leyland 46 seated sleeper from Mandsaur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - The demands of local transport are met with personal vehicles or private auto rickshaw and tempos. Unmetered taxis and auto are available in plenty to commute within Mandsaur. There are a number of private buses, omni bus and jeeps operating within the city and for nearby places. The major public transport of the city is tempos.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong><em>1 - GUPTA RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT NAI ABAADI - (FAMOUS FOR JALEBI, SAMOSA AND KACHORI)</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong><em>2 - SHREE COLD, LOCATED AT NH 79, JANTA COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR CHEESE BURGER)</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong><em>3 - JAINI FOOD, LOCATED AT DASHRATH NAGAR BESIDE SAI MANDIR - (FAMOUS FOR SANDWICHES)</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong><em>4 - SHANKAR SWEETS, LOCATED AT SHUKLA CHOWK, NAYAPURA ROAD, KALAKHET - (FAMOUS FOR KAJU KATLI AND GULAB JAMUN)</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(551, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'MORENA', 'guard-1158823_640.jpg', 'guard-1158823_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Morena is a city and a municipality in Morena district in the Indian state of Madhya Pradesh. It is also known as Muraina and is the administrative headquarters of Morena district and of Chambal Division. It is 39 kms away from Gwalior, Madhya Pradesh. Morena is located at an average elevation of 177 mts above sea level. Legend ascribes the origin of Morena, Madhya Pradesh to a mythological King Putraka who created Morena, Madhya Pradesh by magic for his queen Patali, literally Trumpet flower, which gives it its ancient name Pataligrama. It is said that in honour of the first born to the queen, the city was named Pataliputra. Gram is the Sanskrit for village and Putra means son. Morena, Madhya Pradesh From a scientific history perspective, it would be appropriate to surmise that the history of Morena, Madhya Pradesh started around the year 490 BC when Ajatashatru, the king of Magadh, wanted to shift his capital from the hilly Rajagriha to a more strategically located place to combat the Licchavis of Vaishali. He chose the site on the bank of Ganges and fortified the area. From that time, the city has had a continuous history, a record claimed by few cities in the world. Gautam Buddha passed through this place in the last year of his life, and he had prophesized a great future for this place, but at the same time, he predicted its ruin from flood, fire, and feud.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Morena city has no shortage of hotels and lodging services. There are typically budget luxury hotels, where tourists will get to enjoy all the standard luxuries like AC rooms, LED TV, in-house multi cuisine restaurants etc.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Morena is situated on the national highway 3. The roadway connects all the parts of the state and nearby states such as Rajasthan, Uttar Pradesh with the city.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Though Morena railway station does not enjoy the status of junction, but it is well connected by train services to all parts of the country. Morena is located in between Delhi Bhopal Railway route it takes 4 hours to reach Delhi and 6 hours to reach Bhopal from Morena by train.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The closest major airport to Morena is Gwalior Airport. This airport is in Gwalior and is 40 kms away from the centre of Morena.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - NIKHIL HOTEL,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT MAJOR DISTRICT RD, NIRALA NAGAR, TILAK NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA &nbsp;AND JALEBI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - SHAGUN SWEETS, LOCATED AT NARENDRA NAGAR, AMAIYA COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR CHOWMEIN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - STREET KITCHEN, LOCATED AT BESIDE RAINFOREST ONES MORE,TALA HOUSE ROAD, NEAR CHAKARDHAR CITY - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN ROLLS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - SHRI RAM HOTEL, LOCATED AT NARENDRA NAGAR, AMAIYA COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR DAL FRY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - FLAVOURS, LOCATED AT &nbsp;NEAR GEETA JYOTI SCHOOL - {FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;BUTTERMILK (LASSAI)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - BHOLANATH SWEETS, LOCATED AT MAHADEV NAKA GWALIOR,, STATION RD, JIWAJI GANJ - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORI ANND PURI SABJI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n7 - KOKAM, LOCATED AT MAL GODAM ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR SOMASA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - FAVOURITE LAVLI, &nbsp;LOCATED AT JIWAJI GANJ - (FAMOUS FOR POHA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>9 - MURENA GAJAK BHANDAR, LOCATED AT NEAR HANUMAN MANDIR, SHREE ANTHURAM SHIVHARE CHOWK, GAST KA TAZIA, NAI SADAK, LASHKAR - {FAMOUS FOR TILL BARFI(GAJAK)}</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(552, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'NARSINGHPUR (NARSIMHAPUR)', 'sunset-1097625_6403.jpg', 'sunset-1097625_6404.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Narsinghpur or Narsimhapur, originally known as Chhota Gadarwara, is a city in the Madhya Pradesh state of India. It is renowned for having an ancient temple of Lord Narsingh. Narsinghpur is the administrative headquarters of Narsinghpur district. Geographically it lies at an average elevation of 347 mts above sea level. In the 18th century Jat Sardar, who were the followers of God Narsingh came to this place from Brij. They ruled here for long time and founded the city Narsinghpur. Later they constructed a large temple of Lord Narsingh, where a beautiful idol of Lord Narsimha was placed. The village Gadariya Kheda becomes Narsinghpur which later on turned into the headquarters of the district Narsinghpur. Narsinghpur is famous for its rich agricultural produce. The city is blessed with rich black soil which is usually very fertile and good for agriculture. Farmers employ both old and new agricultural techniques for good crop production. Locals of Narsinghpur or Narsimhapur celebrate National Festival/Mela with great joyous and enthusiasm. On Narsimhapur road, about 25 kms from district headquarters, there is Manegaon where this National Festival is held every year. &nbsp;This festival is organized in the memory of Rudra Pratap Singh. The nearest big town to Narsinghpur is Jabalpur, located at a distance of about 89 kms.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Narsinghpur or Narsimhapur has a number of accommodation options available for the tourists depending on their requirement and budget. These accommodation options include low to medium ranged hotels. Luxury hotels, situated close to many picnic and pilgrim centres, are also available which provides numerous amenities catering to all the needs of the visitors.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Nearest airport to Narsimhapur is the Jabalpur airport, situated about 106 kms far from the city. Jabalpur is well connected by air to all major cities such as Delhi, Mumbai, Kolkata, etc. of the country.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Narsimhapur Railway Station is situated on the Mumbai Kolkata line of the Central Railways. In addition, another nearest railhead to Narsinghpur is at Jabalpur.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Narsimhapur is well connected by road. National Highway 26 and State Highway 22 is the nearest connecting highway to the city of Narsimhapur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - One can avail the services of local/state Government (MPSRTC) bus services to move to Narsimhapur from the nearby and major cities. MPSRTC buses connect Narsimhapur to Seoni, Lakhnadon, Sagar and Kareli.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - PRERNA RESTAURANT, LOCATED IN NARSINGHPUR - (FAMOUS FOR PANEER TIKKA &nbsp;AND VEG MANCHURIAN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - RAM BHAROSE, LOCATED AT KANDELI - (FAMOUS FOR POHA AND JALEBI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - CAFE TOWN, LOCATED IN NARSINGHPUR - (FAMOUS FOR BURGERS AND HOTDOGS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - CHOPATI, LOCATED IN NARSINGHPUR - (FAMOUS FOR PANIPURI AND ALOO TIKKI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - AGRAWAL, LOCATED AT STATION ROAD, KARELI - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;BHEL PURI AND CHAAT)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(553, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'NEEMUCH', 'plumeria-rubra-344074_6402.jpg', 'plumeria-rubra-344074_6403.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Neemuch, a district created on 30th June, 1998 was initially a part of the erstwhile Mandsaur district of Madhya Pradesh. Neemuch was a cantonment town during the British rule, known as the North India Mounted Artillery and Cavalry Headquarters (NIMACH). In 1939, Neemuch was reconverted into the headquarters of the Crown&#39;s Representative Police Force. Thus, Neemuch hold a strong place in terms of cantonment towns in Madhya Pradesh. Neemuch tourism commits itself to its visitors to help them explore and enjoy a variety of sites in and around it. There are some extremely colourful markets around Neemuch. Neemuch has a lot for its visitors, thus becoming among the most preferred places to visit in Madhya Pradesh. Neemuch is a known place that attracts tourists because of its special Moharram processions of Tazia. It is almost 150 years old. This procession marks the martyrdom of Imam Hussain. The district of Neemuch is undoubtedly well known in the entire state. With Neemuch tourism having some wonderful hotspots to offer, visitors are sure to utilize their time to its worth. The best time to visit this place is during the winter season.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Neemuch takes immense pride for being home to many state of the art hotels and also reputed budget hotels. Although there are no international chain of hotels operating in Neemuch as of today, but luxury and service offered by existing 3 Star and 2 Star hotels are pretty much at par with international hotels.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Neemuch doesn&rsquo;t have its own airport. The nearest airport is Ahilyabai Holkar Airport located in Indore, some 273 kms away from Neemuch city. Neemuch and Indore are directly connected only via road.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Neemuch Railway Station is the main railway station and is directly connected to neighbouring districts like Ratlam and Chittorgarh. All the long distance and express trains plying towards Ratlam and Chittorgarh stations halt at Neemuch Railway Station.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Neemuch District&rsquo;s road connectivity is boosted by National Highway 79 and State Highway 31. NH 79 links Neemuch with Ajmer and Chittor in Rajasthan and Ratlam in Madhya Pradesh and SH 31 connects Neemuch to Bhusawal District of Maharashtra state.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - All the major cities of the state and neighbouring cities like Udaipur are well connected to Neemuch by road. Buses are available all time for passengers travelling from any other part of the state to Neemuch.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Auto rickshaw is unarguably the most popular local mode of transportation in Neemuch. Besides, tempos also ply in huge number on the roads of the city. And lastly, private jeeps too today are an integral part of Neemuch transportation system.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - NAKODA THE FAMILY RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT NEEMUCH CHAWNI - (FAMOUS FOR CHILLY PANEER, TANDOORI ROTI AND KAJU CURRY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - JAINI FAST FOOD, LOCATED AT 18 TIT COLONY GOMABAI ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA AND SANDWICH)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - JAGDAMBY, LOCATED AT DASHARA MAIDAN - (FAMOUS FOR CHAT ITEMS0</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - RATAN SWEETS, LOCATED AT VIKAS MARG - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - KAILASH, LOCATED AT NAGAR PALIKA COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR PAW BHAJI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - SATGURU BAKERY, LOCATED AT CRPF ROAD, NAGAR PALIKA COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR SPRING ROLL AND CAKES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - RUPJIBA &nbsp;AND SONS, LOCATED AT BHAGHANA - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSAS, KACHORIS, JALEBIS)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(554, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'PANNA', 'tiger-708022_640.jpg', 'tiger-708022_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Panna is an Indian city located in the state of Madhya Pradesh and is known famous for its diamond mines. Panna diamonds, though not world class in quality and clarity, are famously auctioned off by the District Magistrate at the end of each month. The city also holds a lot of religious importance for the Hindus. It was here that Mahamati Prannath preached the message of self awakening and also unfurled the flag of Jagani. It is believed that the Mahamati decided to take his Samadhi in Panna after having spent eleven years here along with his disciples. The only Diamond City in India is Panna. Panna is beautifully calm and serene roll on meadows dotted with evergreen trees, hills, forests Panna is famous for its temples which strikes a very fine blend of Hindu and Muslim architecture. Panna is the most sacrosanct pilgrimage for the followers of the Pranami sect world over. With a sanctuary for rare wild life and avifauna &amp; a diamond mine, Panna has transformed a royal past into a vibrant and lively present. Panna has been given the award of Excellence the best maintained Tourist Friendly Nation Park of the Country by the Ministry of Tourism. Panna tourism draws largely from the presence of Panna National Park though the Pandava Caves and fall are equally popular. Nature lovers are sure to get a great treat in this beautiful city of Madhya Pradesh due to the parks and scenic picnic spots abounding in the place. The geographical location of Panna renders a sub tropical climate that makes it a dream to travel to the place between the months of October and April.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Panna has good range of hotels in its vicinity. One might easily find a variety of hotels here ranging from 2 stars to 4 star hotels with each hotel having all the basic facilities that include air conditioners as well.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Panna Airport is currently non functional, the nearest working airport is Khajuraho Airport which is 29 kms away.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Tourist and state owned buses connects Panna to all major cities in the state. State owned public bus services are available from Jhansi to Panna at regular intervals. Khajuraho also provides the same facilities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Panna does not have a station of its own. Nearest railway station is Satna 75 kms away, but not all trains take a halt here. The nearest major railway station is Jhansi which is 176 kms away from Panna and all the trains halt at this station.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Panna is just like another city with Taxis, local buses and auto rickshaws as the best way of commuting within the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - KESARVANI, LOCATED AT BENISAGAR MOHALLA - (FAMOUS FOR KHOPRAPAK IS A DESERT MADE FROM MILK, COCONUT, SAFFRON, CARDAMOM AND GARNISH WITH ALMOND AND PISTACHIO</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - SHREENATH, LOCATED AT KATRA BAZAR KOTWALI RD, KATRA MOHALLA - (FAMOUS FOR PAV BHAJI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - SRI BALDEV SWEETS, LOCATED AT BUS STAND RD, BENISAGAR MOHALLA - (FAMOUS FOR BOONDI KA LADDOO)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(555, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'RAISEN', 'ruins-682171_640.jpg', 'ruins-682171_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">It is bounded in the west by Sehore district, in the north by Vidisha district, in the ease and south east by Sagar district, in the south east by Narsimhapur district, and in the south by Hoshangabad and Sehore district. The total area of the district is 8395 sq kms. Raisen, renowned for Raisen Fort, is a city situated in the central part of Madhya Pradesh, India. The city is an administrative headquarters of Raisen district and also forms the part of Bhopal Division. Perched at an altitude of 1461 ft, Raisen city lies between 23 degrees 19 minutes north latitudes and 77 degrees 46 minutes east longitudes. Raisen derives its name from the huge and magnificent Raisen Fort situated in the city. It is alleged that the Raisen was established by a Hindu ruler, Rai Singh in the year 1143 AD. During his reign he constructed a fort on the hill atop which is renowned as Raisen Fort. Raisen is a picturesque city with hills and forests all around the region. It is one of the popular places among the tourists. Locals of Raisen depend on agriculture. The crops cultivated here mainly include wheat, pea and soybean. The nearest big town to Raisen is Bhopal, at a distance of about 42 kms. During the Mugal period Khamkhera was the head quarter of the area noe falls in Gairatganj Tehsil. It receives its present name during the same Mugal rule. Shahpur was the head quarter of the Pargana. Later on it was shifted to Sagoni, which falls in Begamganj Tehsil.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Raisen has a number of accommodation options available for the tourists depending on their requirements and budget. These accommodation options include low to medium ranged hotels.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">By Air - The nearest airport to Raisen is the Bhopal airport which is about 48 km. Bhopal is connected by air to all major cities such as Delhi, Mumbai, Lucknow, Kolkata etc. Regular local and prepaid taxies ply from airport to Raisen.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Bhopal junction is the nearest railhead to Raisen. Bhopal is well connected with regular trains with the rest of the country. One can choose from a number of trains to get to Bhopal and from there Raisen can be easily reached by bus/taxi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Raisen is well connected by road. Once you enter the city, you can take benefits of local buses, autos and taxi services to commute to your desired destination within the city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- One can avail the services of local/state owned Government (UPSRTC) bus services to move to Raisen from the nearby and major cities, such as Bhopal, Jabalpur, etc. Opting for bus can be a good option in case one is looking to cover short distances, for instance, from Raisen to Bhopal.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - HARI OM SWEET &amp; COLDRINK HOUSE, LOCATED IN RAISEN - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - KWALITY SWEETS, LOCATED AT &nbsp;H-7, B, RAISEN RD, PIPLANI, SONAGIRI - (FAMOUS FOR ICECREAM)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - PAPPU NAMKEEN &amp; BAKERY, LOCATED AT SHOP NO. 10, HOUSING BOARD COMPLEX, RAISEN RD, SECTOR A, NEW ASHOKA GARDEN - (FAMOUS FOR PASTRIES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - NEW BANARSI, LOCATED AT &nbsp;MP SH 19, RAISEN - (FAMOUS FOR PAAN)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '');
