(556, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'RAJGARH', 'karnataka-204160_640.jpg', 'karnataka-204160_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Rajgarh district is a district of Madhya Pradesh state in central India. The city of Rajgarh is the administrative headquarters of the district. The district has an area of 6154 sq kms and lies on the northern edge of the Malwa plateau, and the Parbati River forms the eastern boundary of the district, while the Kali Sindh River forms the western boundary. The district has seven tehsils, Rajgarh, Khilchipur, Jirapur, Biaora, Narsinghgarh, Sarangpur and Pachore. The district is bounded by Rajasthan state to the north, and by the districts of Guna to the northeast, Bhopal to the east, Sehore to the southeast, and Shajapur to the south and west. It is part of Bhopal Division. The district was created May 1948, and includes the territory of the former princely states of Rajgarh, Narsinghgarh, Khilchipur, and parts of the states of Dewas Junior and Senior and Indore. In addition to the town of Rajgarh, Khilchipur, Kotravihar and Narsinghgarh are places of interest.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Rajgarh has some deluxe and many medium to budget accommodation options.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Nearest airport to Rajgarh is Bhopal Airport at a distance of about 85 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Rajgarh does not have its own railway station the nearest railhead is located at Biyavra Rajgarh railway station at a distance of about 20 kms from Rajgarh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Rajgarh is well connected to various cities and states via regular state govt. and private buses. Distance between Bhopal to Rajgarh is 298 kms by Road.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - M2 RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT JHABUA - (FAMOUS FOR SOUTH INDIAN FOOD, SANDWICHES AND FRUITJUICES)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(557, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'RATLAM', 'black-and-white-1283789_640.jpg', 'black-and-white-1283789_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Ratlam is a district located in the North West part of Malwa region of Madhya Pradesh and was founded in June 1948. It was later reorganized in the year 1949. Ratlam has a very good market for gold and silver jewellery with Chandi Chowk being the prime area of sale of gold and silver ornaments. Ratlam has a large number of tourist attractions as well as a number of temples. Ratlam is a historical destination, originally called Ratnapuri, in the Malwa region of Madhya Pradesh. The place is bounded in the west by Chittaurgarh district in Rajasthan state. Ratlam district was shaped in the year of 1948 just after India&#39;s independence. The city is popular for its historical and ancient religious monuments. A part of its historical background tells us that this place was famous for the production and trade of opium and tobacco. The place is now very famous for production of Chemicals, Copper wires, Perfumes &amp; pottery and textile. Tourists can get all this information from Ratlam travel guide. Ratlam literally translates to city of precious jewels. Ratlam is very well known for Gold, Ratlami Sev and the Ratlami Sari. Ratlam station is believed to be one of the busiest railway stations in India. Ratlam is surrounded with lots of picnic spots in all the directions. At the one end the JVL temple which is a huge and very beautiful place for visit. And at another end the Paryavaran Park which is famous for its location. And the most famous is Kalika Mata Mandir at the centre of Ratlam. It is also surrounded by ample of waterfalls at the outskirts like Jaman Patli, Kedareshwar, Isarthuni and many more.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Ratlam is an emerging city with variety of hotels in its vicinity. Travellers can find hotels according to their budget. The city has both luxury as well as deluxe hotels to serve its customers. Some of these hotels also provide dining facility. Few hotels in the city operates bar during the night. Most of the hotels do not charge any cancellation fees and provides reasonable rates. In order to get the best hotel plan, one must compare the prices and must consult travel agent if required.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest airport to Ratlam is Indore airport, which is 104 kms away from the city. Dabok Airport, Udaipur is also 190 kms away from Ratlam, which can be taken as an alternative route for reaching the town.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>By Road</strong> - Ratlam is well connected to all the cities through smooth roads and national highways. Buses, cars and taxis are the major sources available that link the place to other places and vice versa.<br />\r\n<strong>&nbsp;<br />\r\nBy Rail</strong> - Regular trains ply from Ratlam to other major cities of the nation, hence making it easily accessible place for everyone. Local transport buses, taxis and cabs can be taken from the station to reach the city and vice versa.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(558, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'REWA', 'BBBB1.jpg', 'BBBB2.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Rewa is a town situated in the Rewa district of Madhya Pradesh. The place is also the district headquarter. Rewa tourism is renowned for its famous museums, forts, waterfalls and historical villages. Apart from all these natural and manmade beauties in Rewa, it is also famous for white tigers. The place is divided into four parts which are known as Binjh Pahar, Lower Northern Plain, Kymore Pahar and the Rewa Plateau. Besides touring at the tiger reserve, Rewa tourism also offers a few exciting places that include Baghael Museum, Rewa Fort, Pili Kothi, Govindgarh Fort, Govindgarh Palace, Venkat Bhavan, Rani Talab, APS University Stadium, Bhairom Baba Statue, Ranipur Karchulian, Keonti Waterfalls, Purva Waterfalls and Chachai Waterfalls. The town derives its name from the district. Moreover, Rewa is the second name for the river Narmada. According to the legends, it is believed that during the 3rd century BC, the existing territories of the district were ruled by the Maurya emperors. It is said that the very first white tiger was trapped in Rewa. The monsoon season is the ideal time to travel to this town. Monsoon sets in July and continues till September and during this time the town is at its scenic best.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Rewa may not have ultra luxurious 5 star and 3 star hotels, but it does have decent number of budget and luxury hotels. These hotels offer all the standard luxurious facilities like A/C rooms, LED TV, 24 hours room services, multi cuisine restaurants and many other important facilities at immensely affordable tariffs. In other words, they are completely value for money hotels. Names and address of all such hotels operating in Rewa have been mentioned below.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Travellers can reach Rewa by getting down at the Khajuraho Airport which is located nearby Rewa. From Khajuraho visitors can take a regular bus to reach Rewa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The Rewa Railway Station is situated at just 5.8 kms from the town of Rewa. Trains from various places in Madhya Pradesh and other parts of India pass through this railway station at regular intervals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Travellers can avail buses to and from Rewa to all the other major towns in the area. Travellers can reach Rewa by car also which takes around two hours and ten minutes from Khajuraho which is located at 169 kms from Rewa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- With three important National Highways passing through Rewa district its connectivity with rest of India can be termed as pretty solid. These three important National Highways are NH 7, NH 27 and NH 75. Amongst these three NH 7 is biggest and also the most important one.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Rewa public transportation mainly compromises of auto rickshaws followed by local bus service, although both these services are mainly concentrated in main city Rewa.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(559, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'SATNA', 'orange-sunset-1424472_640.jpg', 'orange-sunset-1424472_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Satna is a quaint city situated in the state of Madhya Pradesh. It holds in its bossom the glorious past of ancient India and is a treasure trove of religious and mythological memoirs. Historically a portion of the erstwhile Baghelkhand region, Satna district proudly boasts of its proximity to the ancient city of Bharhut and the world renowned Khajuraho temples which is noteworthy of Satna tourism. The sheer abundance of limestone and dolomite in Satna make it one of the largest cement producing districts in the world. There are several cement factories in Satna making cement production the main contributor to the local economy. Attractions in Satna district include a mix of religious and ancient culture. Among the religious destinations, Chitrakoot Dham and Maihar are very important while others include the Sai Baba Mandir in Dhawari, Sharadha Devi Temple and Venkatesh Temple. Other attractions include the Madhavgarh Fort, Gidhakoot and Jagatdev Talab. While in Satna, one must not miss out on eating the locally famous Poha-Jalebi, Lotan ki Mungaudi and Dahi Vada. Typical of the climatic characteristics in most of Madhya Pradesh Satna experiences soaring temperatures in summer, pleasant downpour in the monsoons and chilly weather in the season of winter. The months between October and March are the best and busiest for Satna tourism.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Satna city has innumerable budget luxury hotels, where luxurious accommodation is offered at very bear minimum cost. But make no mistake about the quality of luxury in these hotels, they are absolutely world class and in par with international standards. This is what makes these hotels most desirable hotels of Satna city, not just among tourists but also among locals of Satna.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Satna is equipped with a small airport known as the Satna Airport. However, it is not connected with most of the major places of India. The closest major airport is approximately 220 kilometres away at Jabalpur. From the Jabalpur airport, one can avail taxis to travel to Satna.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Satna has its own railway station and is well connected to several major cities in India. Being positioned on the major route connecting Mumbai and Howrah, Satna Station is a significant junction. Trains are the most convenient mode of transport to reach Satna.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - A couple of state highways and a national highway make the city well connected by roads. Satna is connected to the longest National Highway, NH 7. State highway NH 75 passes from the heart of Satna and connects it to cities of Panna and Rewa which are other important cities of northern Madhya Pradesh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Private and state run buses are available from various cities and towns of Madhya Pradesh and neighbouring Maharashtra to and from Satna. Satna is linked to important cities such as Jabalpur, Bhopal, Indore in Madhya Pradesh and Rewa, Allahabad, Varanasi, etc. outside the state via regular buses.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - ABHINANDAN RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT NATIONAL HIGHWAY 75, RAILWAY COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR KADHAI PANEER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - OM PLAZA, LOCATED AT PANNA KHAJURAHO ROAD, SHAKTI VIHAR, JEEVAN JYOTI COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR CHOWMEIN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - ROYAL FOOD, &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT SHERGANJ, BAGHEDI - {FAMOUS FOR LENTILS(DAL) BATI CHURMA}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - RAVI, LOCATED AT NAVRANG PARK COLONY, BHARHUT NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR DOSA AND IDILI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - LOTAN, LOCATED AT PUSHPRAJ COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR ALOO BADE AND SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - DADDA, LOCATED AT JAGATDEV TALAB RD, JEEVAN JYOTI COLONY - (&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - SATNA - (FAMOUS FOR PHALHARI POTATO CHIWDA IS A SNACK MADE FROM FRIED POTATO STRIPS AND GROUNDNUTS)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(560, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'SEHORE', 'beach-1331405_1280.jpg', 'beach-1331405_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Sehore stands in the foothills of Vindhyachal Range in the middle of Malwa region. Sehore has a long and glorious past. Shaiva, Shakta, Jain, Vaishnav, Budhists and Nath priests made Sehore a significant seat of their deep meditation. Sehore was a part of Bhopal estate. After formation of Madhya Pradesh, the state capital Bhopal was a part of the Sehore district. It was bifurcated in 1972 and a new district Bhopal was formed. Ancient lores indicate that Maharshi Patanjali, the illustrious founder of Yoga sect also spent some time here in prayers &amp; worship. Folklore also indicates to the visits of Lord Rama, Laxman and Sita to its different places. Sehore has so many temples, Mathas, Shrines, Mosques and Churches of great historical and religious antiquity. In that sense, Sehore boasts of its glorious tradition of communal harmony and homogeneous culture. Sidhhapur is the old name of Sehore. According to a rock edict found from the river Seevan, it got its name from Sidrapur. According to an old document Sehore has got its name from the Anglo Indian perversion of Lion as pronounced by the Britishers, since lion were in the great numbers in the nearby jungles. Sehore has been an integral part of Awanti. Later on it was under the tutelage of Magadh dynasty, Chandragupta I, Harshavardhan, Ashoka the great, Raja Bhoj, Peshwa chiefs, Rani Kamlawati and the Nawabs of Bhopal dynasty. Sehore remained the head quarters of the political agent and resident of the British. Sehore played a crucial role in the freedom movement of India.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">While city doesn&rsquo;t have any 5 star hotel, but it does boost decent number of 2 star and 3 star hotels where tourists can enjoy quality luxury accommodation at pretty budget rates. At these hotels one will get to enjoy all the facilities that are usually found in any reputed luxury hotel. This includes 24/7 customer service and even in-house multi cuisine restaurant.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - There is no airport in Sehore. Nearest airport to Sehore is Gwalior Airport about 368 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Sehore station not being directly connected to many important station may cause some inconvenience to commuters, but they can easily do break journey from Bhopal Railway Station.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Bhopal to Sehore is an hour drive of approximately 45 kms and the road is excellent. There are several state and private bus services to and from Sehore to other cities of the country.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - HARSH RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT SINDHI COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR POHA AND JALEBI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - SEHORE RESTAURANT,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT LAAL MASJID SQUARE, OLD SABJI MANDI - (FAMOUS FOR ALOO VADA, SAMOSA &nbsp;AND GUJIYA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - KASHMIRI DHABA, LOCATED AT GULAB VIHAR - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN TIKKA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - MASTER JI SWEETS AND RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT BADA BAZAAR CORNER, MAIN ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - CHAI CHAUPATI, LOCATED AT ENGLISHPURA ROAD NEAR MONALISHA SCHOOL - (FAMOUS FOR VEG SANDWICH AND NOODLES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - SANTOSH MISHTANN BHANDAR, LOCATED AT &nbsp;SHRI RAM COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR BROWN PEDDA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - NEELAM SWEETS, LOCATED AT ENGLISHPURA - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;TEA, SWEETS, SAMOSAS AND KACHORI)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(561, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'SHAHDOL', 'branch-1753736_640.jpg', 'branch-1753736_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Shahdol is named after the headquarters town Shahdol which is located on the Bilaspur Katni Section of the south eastern Railways. The etymology of the name as ascertained from the local residents points to its derivation from the name of the one Shahdolwa Ahir of Sohagpur village. The progenitor of the Ex Illakadar family of Sohagpur, Jamni Bhan was the second son of Maharaja Virbhan Singh of Bagelkhand. He decided to settle at Sohagpur and assured maximum facilities to settler around, and also declared that places settled by clearing forests will be named after the pioneer settlers. Shahdolwa Ahir is believed to have settled the former village of Shahdolwa, about 2.5 kms from the headquarters of Sohagpur after this declaration. Later on, the place used to be the camp site for the Maharaja of Rewa and British officers on tour. More villages were grouped into the village of Shahdol as it grew to a town. The district headquarters was shifted from Umaria to Shahdol after the merger of princely states took place in 1948. With lush green forests, natural wealth of Coal, Minerals and with primitive tribal population, the district Shahdol is situated among the range of Vindhyachal and heading fast in development track. Shahdol is a mix cultural town, there are so many temples made by different societies, like Kali Mandir by Bengali Samiti, Kali mandir by Milan Samiti, Jagannath Temple by Orria Samiti, Gurudwara by Panjabi samiti and sindhi and Jain mandir by jainies and Lord Buddha mandir by Buddhist. Shahdol is a real Indian Town where one can find every kind of cultural activities of different societies of The Indian states.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">To support the footfalls and to provide excellent accommodation to the visitors there are quite a number of star rated and budgeted hotels based in the district. They provide the visitor&rsquo;s with all kinds of facilities and amenities that are required to have a luxurious stay. Most of the hotels are based in prime locations so as to help the travellers roam around the district comfortably. The rates however vary according to accommodation type but in general they are pocket friendly.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport to Shahdol is the Jabalpur Airport or the Dumma Airport. The distance is nearly 150 kms and it takes 3 hrs 30 mins to reach the destination.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Railway connectivity is the best mode of transportation in Shahdol. Based in Bilaspur division, in the south east central zone lays the Shahdol station with three major platforms. The station does not have any trains starting from the location but it has quite a considerable number of trains passing through from popular locations around.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - The district is well connected with several district in and around Shahdol by bus routes provided by Government buses under Madhya Pradesh State Transport Department. Apart from Government buses, there are private buses available in these routes also which may have a little more fare from the government buses but travels regularly and in time with same comfort level.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - There is multiple transport option for Shahdol. Within the district there are local and private buses, private taxis and auto rickshaws to enjoy smooth travel.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - FAST FOOD CORNER, LOCATED AT PANDAV NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR PANEER SPRING ROLL)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - BURGER POINT, LOCATED AT ITWARI MOHALLA - (FAMOUS FOR BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - PET POOJA, LOCATED AT ITWARI MOHALLA - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - RABBY, LOCATED AT PANDAV NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR IDLI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - JAI SWEET MART, LOCATED AT MP SH 9, ITWARI MOHALLA - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;CAKE&#39;S &amp; PASTRY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - SHAHDOL - {FAMOUS FOR PEACE PILAF &nbsp;IS A TYPE OF PULAO MADE FROM GREEN PEAS, FRY RICE, SPICES, CARDAMOM, CLOVES AND CARROTS AND SERVED WITH CURD AND DAAL}</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(562, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'SHAJAPUR', 'india-771288_12804.jpg', 'india-771288_12805.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Shajapur is a town in Malwa region of Madhya Pradesh state in west central India. It is the administrative headquarters of Shajapur district. Shajapur is named after the Mughal emperor Shahjahan, who stopped there in 1640. The original name was Shahjahanpur, which was later shortened to Shajapur. In the 18th century the town became part of the dominion of the Maratha leader Sindhia, founder of the state of Gwalior, and was the headquarters of a district of Gwalior state until Indian independence in 1947. After Independence, Shajapur and its district became part of Madhya Bharat state, which was merged into Madhya Pradesh on 1st November 1956. Shajapur was recognised at the time of Shahjahan. Observing the natural beauty of this area, Fauj of Shahjahan decided to take a halt here. This place was known as Khankarakhedi. Shahjahan and his fauj liked this place very much and consequently when Shahjahan became Samrat he considered the importance of this place for his Southern campaign. In 1640 Meer Bigo was appointed here as Koutwal. He with Shri jagannath Rawal prepared four dwars in four directions. In centre a marketing centre was developed. Consequently this area was populated gradually and converted in colony. Surrounding this place a wall was also prepared. Then in respect of king Shahjahan it was named as Shahjahanpur. After downfall of Mughal dynasty, Shahjahanpur was brought in the Scindia state in 1732 and so many administrative changes were performed. The name Shahjahanpur was now Shajapur in this period only. A beautiful palace in the fort was also developed by Tarabai. In 1904 it was declared as a district.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are some deluxe and a lot of medium to budget accommodation options nearby Rajgarh.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest airport to Shajapur is Devi Ahilyabai Holkar International Airport, Indore which is 92 kms away from Shajapur city centre.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- The nearest railway station to Shajapur is Maksi Railway Station which is 23 kms away from Shajapur city centre.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - There are regular buses from other major cities of the country to Shajapur.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - TULARAM DADA, LOCATED IN SHAJAPUR - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - SAMRAT, LOCATED AT BUSTAND - {FAMOUS FOR LASSI (BUTTERMILK)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - RATHORE CAFE HOUSE, LOCATED IN SHAJAPUR - (&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;FAMOUS FOR COFFEE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - APNA SWEETS, LOCATED AT NEAR ROADWAYS BOOKING OFFICE , BUS STAND - (FAMOUS FOR SOHAN PAPADI, KAJU BARFI AND BHUJIYA SEV}</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(563, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'SHEOPUR', 'tiger-165073_6401.jpg', 'tiger-165073_6402.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Sheopur is located at northern part of Madhya Pradesh. Some of the main locations are Vijaypur, Karahal and Baroda. Major tourist attraction is Palpur wildlife sanctuary. The well known Kaketa reservoir is located in this district. The art of woodcarving has flourished in district Sheopur and the beautifully embellished wooden ceilings, doors and lintels with finely carved designs are silent testimonials of its glory. The wood carvers of Sheopur, with great sensitivity and skill transform different varieties of wood. The crafts persons of Sheopur make pipes, masks, toys, doors, stands, windows, wooden memorials, flower vases, bedposts and cradle posts etc. There is no conclusive documented source available to tracing the historical origin of Sheopur Fort. However a Jain pillar edict dated 1026 AD refers to the existence of the Sheopur fort. The 11th AD the famous poet Khadag Rai of Gwalior in his renowned work Gopanchal Akyan mentions Sheopur. The 225 years history of the Sipahad kingdom as it is called a saga of untold valour and forcefully independent cultural identity. This is reflected there architectural remains, which are individual thriving tradition of performing art, paintings, sculpture and highly artistic style of living. The individual palace of Narsingh Gaur, Rani Mahal or Goojri mahal are striking examples of Gaur architecture.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>City has limited variations of accomodation for visitors.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air</strong> - Nearest Airport to Sheopur is Rajmata Vijaya Raje Scindia Airport, Gwalior at about 210 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Train </strong>- Nearest Railway station to Sheopur is Sheopur Kalan Railway station.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Road</strong> - Sheopur is connected by regular bus services with Gwalior, Morena, Shivpuri and Kota. Sheopur is 210 kms away from Gwalior, 120 kms from Shivpuri and 230 kms from Morena.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - MEENA RESTORENT UTANWAD, LOCATED AT UTANBAD - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - JAIN SWEETS, LOCATED IN SHEOPUR - (FAMOUS FOR GULAB JAMUN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - MARWARI SWEETS, LOCATED AT M S ROAD, SHEOPUR - (FAMOUS FOR KHOYA KI BARFI)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(564, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'SHIVPURI', 'india-1379282_1280.jpg', 'india-1379282_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Shivpuri is an ancient town and a sacred place. It was formerly known as Sipri. It received its current name after independence in honour of the God Shiva. It is steeped in the royal legacy of its past, when it was the summer capital of the Scindia rulers of Gwalior. Earlier to that, Shivpuri&#39;s dense forests were the hunting grounds of the Mughal emperors. Emperor Akbar captured herds of elephants for his stables while returning from Mandu in year 1564. The thick forests are still there and continue to be a source of forest produce for domestic and industrial use. Shivpuri was awarded as Jagir to the Kachwahas of Narwar in the 17th century. Shivpuri king and fort was won by Ranoji Bhoite a Maratha General of Chhatrapati of Satara on instructions of Jankoji Shinde, Gwalior Chief. In February 1781, the Scindias lost a battle to the British there, which resulted in a mutual defense treaty the following October. Shivpuri again came under the rule of the Scindias in 1804, who granted it to one of their Maratha generals by name Ingle. Later, it was transferred to the HEIC in 1817 under a treaty, but the Scindias regained it in 1818. Tantya Tope was awarded death sentence on 17th April 1859 by British Raj for his part in the Revolt of 1857 in nearby Jhansi. He was hanged to death in Shivpuri, at a site near the present collectorate.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are many hotels in Shivpuri also that offers a comfortable stay for all sorts of travellers. Most of them offer high quality of hospitality and services. The luxury hotels provide the multi-cuisine restaurant also along with continental cuisine.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Nearest airport is at Gwalior which is about 112 kms, which is connected with regular flights from Delhi &amp; Bhopal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Nearest railheads are at Jhansi about 101 kms and Gwalior which are on the Delhi Chennai main lines.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- &nbsp;Shivpuri is well connected by road to several cities of India. Shivpuri is connected by regular bus services with Gwalior, Indore, Bhopal, Jhansi and Ujjain.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SHRI NATH, LOCATED AT CHORAHA, PRAGATI BAZAR, BANK COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR PAVV BHAJI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - REHMAT CORNER, LOCATED AT GOVIND PURA - (FAMOUS FOR BIRYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - EAT STREET, LOCATED AT GURUDWARA ROAD, IN FRONT OF AIRTEL OFFICE, M.P., TARKESHWARI COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;SANDWICHES AND CHOCOLATE FUDGE(IS A TYPE OF &nbsp;CONFECTIONERY MADE FROM SUGAR, BUTTER AND MILK)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - SESAI WALA MISTHAN BHANDAR, &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT ADARSH NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR MALPUA IS A TYPE OF SWEET PANCAKE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - SHIVPURI - {FAMOUS FOR KOPRA PAK (COCONUT BARFI) IS A SWEET &nbsp;MADE FROM GRATED COCONUT, SUGAR, MILK AND MAWA}</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(565, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'SIDHI', 'sunset-785085_640.jpg', 'sunset-785085_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Sidhi is a district in the Indian state of Madhya Pradesh. This is the charming city of the Madhya Pradesh. Sidhi district is a symbol of natural, historical and cultural history. This district is well known for its luxuriant natural resources with the river Sone draining the district. Sidhi district forms parts of the hill Kaimour range of mountains. On one side the spectrum of its floristic socio cultural diversity and ethnic history of tribal, the district has a panoramic view of the Kaimur, Kehejua and Ranimunda hills blazing with flowers of flame of forest and intoxicated by the sweet smell of Mahua flowers. There are many places to visit in the Sidhi district. The peoples further visited this district due to its beautiful sites.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The hotels in Sidhi offer 24 hours front desk facility. All rooms are equipped with amenities like wake-up calls, adjustable windows, wardrobe, seating area and an attached bathroom with hot and cold water facility. Hotels in Sidhi provide various services like laundry, medical and room service are available at the hotel.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Nearest Airport to Sidhi is Rewa Airport, Rewa at a distance of about 115 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Nearest Railway station to Sidhi is Niwas Road Railway station at Mahuagaon at about 48 kms from Sidhi city centre.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> &nbsp;- Nearest Bus stand to Sidhi is Sidhi Bus stand. There are regular buses to and from Sidhi to nearby cities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - MADHURAM RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT WARD NUMBER 10 - (FAMOUS FOR MANCHURIAN AND PANEER CHOWMEEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - BHARAT, LOCATED IN SIDHI - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - FINGERS MAGIC FUNFOODS, LOCATED AT KUBER COMPLEX (GOL MARKET), COLLECTORATE ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA AND SANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - PATHAK DHABA, LOCATED AT NEAR HP PETROL PUMP, BAHARI - (FAMOUS FOR KHEER)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(566, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'TIKAMGARH', 'divider-223588_640.jpg', 'divider-223588_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Tikamgarh is one of the prominent cities located in northern Madhya Pradesh State. More importantly, it serves as districts headquarter of Tikamgarh district, one of the 50 districts of Madhya Pradesh State. On the outside, Tikamgarh looks like any other small town city struggling to achieve economic viability, but when one starts to scan through the city one will be pleasantly surprised to discover that this city and its adjoining towns are filled with many beautiful temples, forts and palaces. All these landmarks are symbolic of this city&rsquo;s glorious history. Tikamgarh district lies in the northern part of Madhya Pradesh. The early history of Tikamgarh district is however not chronicled, though as suggested by the numerous ruins of buildings and other old remains lies scattered at various places, viz Orchha, Garh Kudar, Prithvipur, Barana, Lidhoura, Digora, Mohangarh, Baldeogarh and Tikamgarh, it must be having a glorious past. The district was the part of vast empires successively ruled by the Mauryas, the Sungas and the imperial Guptas. It was in the first quarter of 9th century AD, that Mannuka founded a new dynasty the Chandel dynasty in this area. Tikamgarh along with Khajuraho and Mahoba formed part of extensive Chandel Kingdom. The Khangras also held this region especially around Garh Kundar. The rising power of Bundelas in this region resulted into the downfall of the Khangras. The Orchha records trace the descent of the Bundela Kingdom of Orchha from Garh Kudar chiefs of Benaras Hemkaran, also known as Pancham Bundela.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">There are some really good luxury hotels operating in the heart of Tikamgarh city as well as in Orchha town. Orchha town is located approximately 100 kms away from Tikamgarh city. Being one of the primary tourist attractions Tikamgarh is home to some really good hotels. Tourists can prefer to stay in these hotels as they are equipped with all facilities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air </strong>- Khajuraho is the nearest airport about 125 kms from where there is a daily flight for Delhi &amp; Agra which comes under Chhatarpur district.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Train</strong> - The construction of railway line to Tikamgarh has been completed in 2012. On 26th April 2013 was connected with railway services. The rail services began from Lalitpur passenger train. The railway line between Tikamgarh and Lalitpur rail route is 40 kms long.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Road</strong> - Tikamgarh is well connected by road. There are daily services of buses for every part of state.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - As for local transportation is concerned, then there are decent number of auto rickshaws plying through the city, but absence of city bus service does make local transportation very lethargic.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(567, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'UMARIA', 'waterfall-817350_640.jpg', 'waterfall-817350_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Umaria is a town in Umaria district of the Shahdol division of Madhya Pradesh state of central India. There are so many places to visit in the Umaria city, which attracts a lot of tourists from different parts of the country. It is situated at a distance of about 69 kms from Shahdol. Near the railway station stands a Siva temple, known as the Sagara temple. It was an old shrine, recently remodelled. Its main gates are still intact with beautiful stone statues, carved in Khajuraho models. Near about is Jwalamukhi temple. About 6.5 kms away from the town, there is another temple, with similar carvings of the Khajuraho pattern. It is known as the Mariwal temple. These all have a unique charm to gather the peoples of all the religion in the one place. Umaria is an important north eastern district of Madhya Pradesh. The town of Umaria is the district headquarters. The district is part of Shahdol Division. Umaria is enriched with its vast resources of forests and minerals. The coal mines are a steady source of revenue for the district. The most important mineral found in the district is coal and as a result 8 mines are being operated by South Eastern Coalfields Limited in the district. The famous Bandhavgarh National Park and Sanjay Gandhi Thermal Power Station at Mangthar are located in the district. The Bandhavgarh National Park and Sanjay Gandhi Thermal Power Station Mangthar are two places of worth visiting in Umaria district. In fact, Umaria, a small village, is the getaway city to the popular Bandhavgarh National Park.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Umaria is one of the most preferred tourist destinations especially for the adventure lovers due to the presence of Bandhavgarh in its area. Though Bandhavgarhh has various high rated as well as economical hotels close to the park there are some in the heartland of Umaria district which gives better access to both the sightseeing spots in the district as well as to Bandhavgarh. There are multiple hotels with almost all necessary facilities but in different price range. Comfort and hygiene, facilities and amenities are never a problem in the hotels of Umaria.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- 190 kms away from Umaria is situated the Dumna Airport, Jabalpur. There are several domestic airlines operating to and from Agra, Delhi, and Varanasi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The closest railhead is the town of Umaria, which is 30 kms from Bandhavgarh. It is linked by train to cities in Madhya Pradesh and other states, including Delhi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Private and state owned bus services operate regular buses to Umaria from Bandhavgarh, Jabalpur, and other towns in Madhya Pradesh. Taxis too can be hired to get to Umaria.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Getting around the thick forest of Bandhavgarh can be either done by hiring a jeep or riding through the jungle on elephant back.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - KRISHNA RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT STATION ROAD, NH 78 - (FAMOUS FOR DAL FRY AND PANEER BUTTER MASALA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - MANMOUJI SWEETS, LOCATED AT STATION ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR CAKES, COOKIES)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - CHOUPATI, LOCATED IN UMARIA - (FAMOUS FOR PHULKI(PANIPURI, IDLI, DOSA, CHOWMIN, FRIED RICE, SAMOSA, ICECREAM)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(568, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'VIDISHA', 'ancient-1550761_640.jpg', 'ancient-1550761_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Vidisha or Bhilsa as it was called during the medieval period is a city of ancient remnants and monuments of historical significance. The remains of the ancient town of Besanagar and the Udayagiri Caves are examples of the long lost glory of the ancient Gupta Empire. The city is in the state of Madhya Pradesh and is located close to Bhopal, the capital of the state. As you walk through the history packed by lanes of Vidisha, you might marvel at this major trade centre from nearly 2600 years ago. Once you reach here, you might want to stand still for a minute and imagine a Shah Rukh Khan from the movie Ashoka meandering through this smallish city in a galloping white horse. Tourism in Vidisha forms the major part of economic activity of the place. Vidisha tourism has many places of religious and historical importance to offer to its travellers. There are many noted sculptures and inscriptions, ruins and archaeological sites too. Sironj is a famous pilgrim centre for the Jain community in Vidisha. Another popular hotspot in Vidisha is the Heliodorus Pillar, which is also called Khamba Baba. The Udaygiri Caves is one of the most prominent attractions of Vidisha Tourism. Vidisha can be visited during the monsoon season and the winter seasons. During these seasons, the weather remains pleasant and beautiful. But the best season to visit is the winter season during the period from October to March.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">With many tourists visiting this place, stay is never a problem. There are many hotels around this city that caters to everyone&#39;s needs in terms of pricing, accommodation etc. Tourists can choose anything depending on their needs and budget.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\n<strong>By Air</strong> - Raja Bhoj Airport in Bhopal is the closest airport to reach Vidisha. Bhopal airport is well connected with all major Indian airports like Delhi, Mumbai, Gwalior and Indore. Vidisha is nearly 56 kms away from the airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - To reach Vidisha by rail, the easiest way is to get down at the Vidisha Railway Station itself. It is a major station in the Delhi Chennai track. The Vidisha station is connected to all the major railway stations in India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Vidisha is well connected with all the neighbouring cities and town via road. There are taxi services available and also a plenty of private and state government bus services. There are also frequent bus services available from Bhopal to Vidisha and back. Buses also ply from Udaipur to Vidisha.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Vidisha is well connected with all the neighbouring cities and town via road. There are taxi services available and also a plenty of private and state government bus services. There are also frequent bus services available from Bhopal to Vidisha and back. Buses also ply from Udaipur to Vidisha.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - EAT STREET RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT INDIRA NAGAR, SHASTRI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR PASTA AND NOODLES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - ADDA, LOCATED AT SHERPURA - (FAMOUS FOR PANEER TIKKA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - BRIJ, LOCATED AT NANDWANA ROAD, BARIPURA - {FAMOUS FOR BUTTERMILK (LASSI)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - NEW VATIKA FAMILY RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT SALAMATPUR, SH-19, VIDISHA ROAD, RAISEN - (FAMOUS FOR DAL FRY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - BHAGDI DHABA AND RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT DEWANGANJ, BHOPAL, SH-19, VIDISHA ROAD, RAISEN - {FAMOUS FOR EGGPLANT PUREE (BAIGAN KA BHARTA )}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - HARI OM SWEET AND COLDRINK HOUSE, LOCATED AT &nbsp;RAISEN - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(569, 14, 31, 757, 'West Bengal', 'INDIA', 'ASANSOL', 'water-lily-1210721_640.jpg', 'water-lily-1210721_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The second largest city of West Bengal, Asansol, is famous for its industrial set up and coal mining. Located in the Burdwan District, the city has reputed educational institutions. It is home to a large workforce and has excellent transportation facilities and thus is an ideal place for commerce and trade. There are many dams, parks, picnic spots and religious sites to visit in Asansol. Asansol City Guide is incomplete without a mention of its industrial prowess. Asansol is a heavily industrialized region and houses many giant market players like Eastern and IISCO Steel Plant, Chittaranjan Locomotive, Damodar Valley Corporation, Disergarh Power Supply, Asansol Cement, Burn Standard, and Hindustan Cables Ltd etc. The roots of the name Asansol can be traced to two different things, the Asan which is a type of tree that grows near River Damodar and Sol &nbsp;a mineral rich land. It is amongst the 11 Indian cities in the list of 100 fastest growing cities in the world with a rank of 42. Asansol was a significant place for congregation of Jains 2500 years ago. The city is beautifully located between the rivers Damodar and Ajay. The picturesque Damodar Valley offers many offbeat travel ideas for people to explore.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Asansol has a lot of medium to budget accommodation options that offer homely comfort and nice food. There are some wonderful medium range and budget range accommodation options.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport is in the city of Kolkata.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - The Asansol railway station is on the Delhi to Howrah route and many trains from different parts of the country pass through the station.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - The city of Asansol is well connected by road. So, one can reach there by taxi or private car.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Bus</strong> - Government buses connect the town to most of the cities in the state and one can reach the place from Kolkata and Howrah.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1- DURGA FOODS&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT G T ROAD, SHANKAR P MURGASOL, G T ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR DAL MAKHANI AND PANEER DISHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - TUK TUK TAWA, LOCATED AT OPPOSITE SBI, MURGASOL, GT ROAD, USHAGRAM - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN TANDOORI &nbsp;AND MOMOS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - NILANJANA RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT BNR MORE, APCAR GARDEN MAIN ROAD, APCAR GARDEN - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN TIKKA MASALA)&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - HIMLAND FAST FOOD CENTRE, LOCATED AT SB GORAI RD, CHELIDANGA - (FAMOUS FOR MUGALI PARATHA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - MADHURI SWEETS, LOCATED AT ASANSOL BAZAR, GT RD, PUCCA BAZAR, MUNSHI BAZAR - (FAMOUS FOR CHOLA BATHURA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - SIP&#39;N&#39; BITE, LOCATED AT CHEESE VADA PAV - (FAMOUS FOR CHEESE VADA PAV)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - CALCUTTA SWEETS, LOCATED AT SEN RALIEGH ROAD, MUNSHI BAZAR - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORI, SAMOSA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n8 - RANJAN CABIN SWEET SHOP, LOCATED AT OPPOSITE KANU GORAI&#39;S MANSION, HUTTON RD, PATHAK BARI - (FAMOUS FOR RASOGOLLA AND RASMALAI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>9 - CHACHI SWEETS (DURGA MISTANA BHANDAR), LOCATED AT 6 S.B, RAHA LANE, PATHAK BARI - (FAMOUS FOR KHASTA KACHURI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>10 - HAZRA SWEETS, LOCATED AT CHELIDANGA MAIN ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR GULAB JAMUN)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '');
