(570, 14, 31, 757, 'West Bengal', 'INDIA', 'BALURGHAT', 'road-1543619_640.jpg', 'road-1543619_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The town of Balurghat is located in the district of Dakshin Dinajpur in the state of West Bengal. It is a well known region for its clean and free from pollution atmosphere. The whole town is loaded with lush green forests and they are host to some of the best picnic spots here. These picnic spots are very popular, not just amongst the local folks, but even with the visitors of the town who can spend great time here relaxing with their families. Two main picnic spots here are Ragunathpur and Doghachii and are very easy to reach from Balurghat and ideal for a day trip. Balurghat Museum is one of the major attractions here and exhibits several artefacts from history that are unique and worth having a look. The museum also showcases Coins, Sculptures, Inscriptions, Ornamental Stones and many exclusive items crafted from Terracotta. The inscriptions showcased here in the museum belong to the period of Pala. Another place to visit is Khanpur, which is located at a distance of 18 kms from the region of Balurghat and is truly worth having a look. A very famous religious site is Bolakali Temple, which is at a distance of nearly 20 kms from Balurghat and is of great importance amongst the local people. Tapan Dighi Lake is a famous tourist destination and last but not the least is the Patiram Thakur Estate.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Balurghat is a small Town and there are not many hotels in the area. Though, there are several govt. guest houses and lodges available within the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - This pollution free city, situated in Dakshin Dinajpur district of West Bengal, does not have its own railway station. The nearest station is at New Jalpaiguri. It is an economical and comfortable way of reaching this undiscovered place.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport to this magnificent place is located at a distance of 290 kms from here. Known by the name Bagdogra Airport, it is located outside the town of Siliguri. This airport is connected to all the major cities of India, making Balurghat accessible from Kolkata, New Delhi, Chennai and Mumbai.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Balurghat is very well connected by road to various cities, like Siliguri and Kolkata. State government run buses are quite frequent from Balurghat to different cities. Apart from government buses, there are many private bus operators which provide bus services to this town.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - BABUN HOTEL, LOCATED AT KHADIMPUR - (FAMOUS FOR TARKA DAL AND MEAT CURRY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - MODAK RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT BALURGHAT ROAD, HILI BALURGHAT HWY, TRIMOHINI, HILI - (FAMOUS FOR GHUGNI IS A SNACK MADE FROM BLACK GRAM OR DRIED YELLOW PEAS OR DRIED WHITE PEAS AND GRAVY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - MANORANJAN SWEET, LOCATED AT RATHTALA - (FAMOUS FOR SHINGARA(SAMOSA) AND KALAKAND)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(571, 14, 31, 757, 'West Bengal', 'INDIA', 'BANKURA', 'india-1453721_6403.jpg', 'india-1453721_6404.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Over recent years with the penetration of tourism into West Bengal getting deeper in to the state, Bankura Township, which is now actually a mini city, has seen a significant upsurge. The city has just around a 150000 inhabitants and is culturally and traditionally very rich with references to it in the Mahabharata. In fact, Bankura also features in Chinese history. Bankura Tourism is flanked with tourist attractions at a short drive from the city. To the west, one can visit the natural hot spring at Susunia Hill which is around 50 kilometres from Bankura. Also to the west is Beharinath Hill which is the tallest in the Bankura district and an important place for Jainism. Much of Bankura tourism&rsquo;s success is also attributed to the huge dam at Muktimanipur, which is around 55 kilometres from Bankura. Muktimanipur is incidentally the second largest earth dam in India. Apart from these Bankura also features many more temples and mosques around the city, each with its own little historical importance. Bankura Tourism is also boosted by the presence of Bengali paintings, music and other forms of local art. Terracotta is also a prevalent modern art in Bankura. Bankura is so influenced by music that a couple of local engineering college bands have actually managed to make it big in talent shows. The best time to visit Bankura is right after the winter and before the summer sets in.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Bankura has several luxury and budget hotels as well as some outstanding lodges located in the city. Some hotels are nestled in the city itself while others are located away from the chaos of the city. All these places of accommodation at Bankura offer well appointed rooms, scrumptious food, hygienic environment and an amiable staff.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">By Air - The closest airport to Bankura is Kokata&rsquo;s Netaji Subhashchandra Bose International airport with connections to major Indian cities and many overseas destinations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">By Train - Bankura has its own railway station with connection to Kolkata and other cities in the state via larger stations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">By Road - Bankura can be accessed by road via State Highway 2 from Kolkata and is a 170 kilometres from the capital.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Local Transport - One can hire rickshaws &amp; auto rickshaws for going around the town. Rental cars can also be hired for the same purpose.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SNACKS CORNER, LOCATED AT KENDUADIHI - (FAMOUS FOR MASALA CHICKEN)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - MONTU DAR, LOCATED AT KATJURIDANGA - (FAMOUS FOR PANIPURI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - GUIRAM SWEET, LOCATED AT RAMPUR ROAD, RAMPUR, BANKURA - (FAMOUS FOR RASOGOLLA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - MAJHIR MISTIR DOKAN, LOCATED AT COLLEGE ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR MASALA COLD DRINK)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - SATI MATA MISTANNA BHANDAR, LOCATED AT BYPASS ROAD, ARABINDA NAGAR SOUT - (FAMOUS FOR DHOKLAS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - BARAT, LOCATED AT PURULIA ROAD, LAKSHMINARAYANPUR - (FAMOUS FOR PEDA IS A SWEET MADE FROM KHOYA AND SUGAR)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(572, 14, 31, 757, 'West Bengal', 'INDIA', 'BERHAMPORE', 'fountain-728562_640.jpg', 'fountain-728562_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Located in the state of West Bengal, Berhampore is a culturally rich place and is the fifth largest city of the state. Being the dwelling place of Brahmin families, the place is known by the name of Brahmapur. It is the civil headquarters of the Murshidabad district. Berhampur city guide is incomplete without a mention of its rich cultural heritage. Some of the popular historic places of interest in close proximity to Berhampore include Old Cossim bazar Palace, Kathgola palace, Char bangla Temple and Katra Masjid etc. Many buildings of the late 1600s can still be seen in Berhampore. A distinguished type of metal known as Khagrai Kansha, used in making bells comes from this city. Berhampore is also recognized for special type of sweets, Chenabora, Manohara, and Khaja. The place was also known as Golden Bengal by the Britishers. The stylish arts of the region are very popular among the tourists. Berhampore is also very popular for the handmade carpets, baskets and the miniature painting made up of jute takes one by surprise and makes one wonder that can jute be utilized so beautifully. The major industries situated here include ivory carving, rice and oil seed milling silk weaving and precious metal working.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are accommodation options, including elite luxury hotels as well as midsized budget ones catering to the needs and demands of people belonging to all sections of the society. The courteous and friendly staff, modern amenities, hygienic ambiance etc contribute to the popularity of these hotels.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest International Airport from Berhampore is the Kolkata Airport at about 190 kms, a convenient option for travellers. The Airport is well connected with other major cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- It has its own Railway Station named as Berhampore Railway Station which is connected to the major cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Regular bus services from Kolkata are available to the Berhampore on a daily basis. Multiple departures are available every day.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center">1 - BERHAMPORE - [FAMOUS FOR PITHAS IS ATYPE OF SNACK PANCAKE MADE FROM RICE FLOUR OR WHEAT FLOUR]<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(573, 14, 31, 757, 'West Bengal', 'INDIA', 'BASIRHAT', 'nature-1541323_640.jpg', 'nature-1541323_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Basirhat is a city as well as a municipality in the North of 24 Parganas district in the State of West Bengal. On the banks of River Ichhamati the city is connected to border of Bangladesh with well road and rail facility to Barasat. Though this place is too small, one can find various hospitals and healthcare clinics, as well as services like police stations, ATMS and banks, and lot more. Along with this, the town is not less than any other administrative services, transportation, and tourism services. The sub division of Basirhat was formed in the year 1861, as per the Government order. This town constitutes Police stations like the Kalinga, Harua and Husenabad. Earlier, Basirhat was under the jurisdiction of the city of Barasat Sub division that was renamed as the Basurhat till the year 1896. While, Basirhat municipality was situated during 1st April 1869, which was separated into 22 wards that covers an area of 22.5 sq kms. Basirhat is not just a city, but also a municipality in the North 24 Parganas district of West Bengal. The city has been established on the river side on the sub divisional town. Basirhat is known for Tebhaga Movement of 1946-47. The peasant movement further boosted the ongoing movements for the independence of India. This beautiful place was developed initially by the families of two people namely the Jhine&#39;s Ghosh and another person was Mir&#39;s of Mirbati. The history behind the popularity of the town is long, but two reasons are birth of Dinesh Chandra Majumder and Swami Brahmananda. Both these legends have been born in the same city, because of which the town has become so popular.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Basirhat offers accommodation in midsized tourist lodges and hotels to stay at reasonable tariff. Tourists could stay at these places. Hotels in Basirhat are both comfortable and affordable to book while your travel to this city of West Bengal. Quality of the hotels in the city of Basirhat is excellent when compared to their metro counterparts.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest airport to Basirhat is Netaji Subhash Chandra Bose Intl. Airport, Kolkata which is 45 kms away from Basirhat city centre.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train </strong>- The nearest railway station to Basirhat is Mallickpur Hat Railway Station which is 31 kms away from Basirhat city centre.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - There are convenient bus services to reach Kolkata as well as some other places from the city of Basirhat.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - KITCHEN KING RESTRURANT, LOCATED AT BASIRHAT - (FAMOUS FOR BIRIYANI AND CHIKEN CHAP)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - MIO AMORE, LOCATED AT BASIRHAT - (FAMOUS FOR VARITIES OF CAKES)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(574, 14, 31, 757, 'West Bengal', 'INDIA', 'BIRBHUM (SANTINIKETAN)', 'birnbaum-leaves-59904_640.jpg', 'birnbaum-leaves-59904_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Popularly known for its literary background, Santiniketan is located around 180 kilometres north of Kolkata in the Birbhum district of West Bengal. Rabindranath Tagore, the Nobel Laureate, made Santiniketan an International University, where the culture and tradition of the east easily transcends with the science of the west. Niketan which means house and Shanti which means peace is a place which is surrounded by blooming beauty amidst the lush green land. Many famous personalities such as Indira Gandhi, Satyajit Ray, Gayatri Devi, Nobel Prize winner Amartya Sen and Abdul Ghani Khan have visited Santiniketan which makes this heritage home a major tourist attraction for both Indians and foreigners. Giving you a slice of radical art, dance and culture, Santiniketan is a cultural hub that cannot be missed. With round the clock events and attractions, Santiniketan is abuzz with celebrations of all kinds. Paush Utsav is celebrated to mark the establishment of a Brahma Mandir at Santiniketan. It is in and around December to January where festival of folk dance, music, art and culture, sports and artifacts can be seen in full swing. Santiniketan is famous for its Bengali food, especially fish curry. The Vishwa Bharati Campus is huge and beautiful. There are other places one can visit near Santiniketan such as the Kankalitala which is a sacred Satipithas, and adjacent to Santiniketan is a deer park which remains closed on Wednesdays.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Santiniketan has a variety of lodges and hotels to suite its guests. Vishva Bharati University itself has four guest houses in the campus area, allowing the visitors to stay in the glorious campus, at moderate rates.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Santiniketan is not equipped with its own airport. Kolkata is the nearest airport from Santiniketan.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Travelling by road is another comfortable option. Santiniketan is well connected by roads. Buses from major surrounding areas like Kolkata, Guwahati and Durgapur are available at nominal prices.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The most convenient way to reach Santiniketan is by train. The nearest station is Bolpor Station which is hardly 2 to 3 kms away.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport -</strong> Commuting in the city is mainly done with tourist cars and cycle rickshaws. However, the best way to explore this beautiful, sleepy town is on foot.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - AHELI RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT NEAR SCHOOL BAGAN, BOLPUR - (FAMOUS FOR EGGROLL)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - THE TAMARIND, LOCATED AT OPPOSITE SBI (CHITRA MORE), BOLPUR - SANTINIKETAN ROAD, SURASHREE PALLY, BOLPUR - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;MASALA DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - BOLPUR CHIMNEY, LOCATED AT &nbsp;SANTINIKETAN RD, SURASHREE PALLY, BOLPUR - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN ROLL)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - GHORE BAIRE, LOCATED AT BOLPUR - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;CHICKEN CURRY AND FISH CURRY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - RAJAN, LOCATED AT SYAMBATI, SANTINIKETAN - {FAMOUS FOR FUCHKA(PANIPURI)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - MAA KANKALI FAST FOOD, LOCATED AT SYAMBATI, SANTINIKETAN - (FAMOUS FOR CHOWMEN AND EGG ROLL)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - SARBA MANGALA, LOCATED AT SANTINIKETAN ROAD, BOLPUR - {FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;KACHURI AND SINGARA(SAMOSA)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(575, 14, 31, 757, 'West Bengal', 'INDIA', 'COOCH BEHAR', 'hibiscus-336940_1280.jpg', 'hibiscus-336940_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Cooch Behar is one of the only planned towns in the northern regions of West Bengal and spells of class and heritage value all the way. Back in the day, the town served as the headquarters of the princely state of Bihar and today is a world famous tourist destination with colonial style buildings on the one hand and the majestic Himalayas on the other. Cooch Behar is located at the foothills of the Eastern Himalayas and snow capped hills put together with vast alpine forests make for the natural setting. Cooch Behar is influenced by various cultures, Bengali, Buddhist and Tibetan alike and is a perfect example of India&rsquo;s cultural diversity. Cooch Behar Tourism offers some very important places for the tourists to visit. Cooch Behar is very proximate to the Torsa River and the monsoons here are notorious with heavy rains rendering the place inaccessible at times. The locals in Cooch Behar are a fun loving lot. Carnivals are hosted here all through the year and the Ras Mela is one of the oldest carnivals in North Bengal. One has to try the various cuisines while at Cooch Behar. Bhuna Khichiri and Labra are local favourites. From roadside dumplings called Momos to the confluence of Bangladeshi and Bengali cuisine, the various roadside stalls, restaurants and eateries offer a varied mix. The locals at Cooch Behar are so closely knit that every neighbourhood called a Para has its own community club, entertainment centre and mess hall. The best time to visit Cooch Behar is during the winter time when the weather is perfect for travelling. Cooch Behar is well connected to the rest of the country.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Cooch Behar is a home to some of the best hotels, lodges and guest houses located. The hotels here have best facilities and all kind of amenities like spacious rooms, hot and cold water, 24 hrs room service, car parking etc so that one can live grandly here. Apart from this they are located in all the best locations across the city which makes communication to various tourist spot easy and quick.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Cooch Behar has its own airport which is currently dysfunctional Bagdogra Airport near Siliguri is the nearest airport. Bagdogra receives flights from the major cities of India and is an important airport linking north east to the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Cooch Behar is extremely well connected by road to the nearby cities. State tourism buses run at a regular interval to and from the town along with private buses which help in increasing connectivity.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - New Cooch Behar is the nearest station, having direct trains from the key cities of the country and connected trains from others. Jalpaiguri and Siliguri railway stations connect Cooch Behar to the rest of the state and the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Travellers can use buses and shared rickshaw for travelling from one destination to the other. Since Cooch Behar is a small town and destinations are nearby, travellers can also travel on foot from one place to another.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - ABHI&#39;S JUICE CAFE, LOCATED AT SUNITY ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR SHAKES AND JUICE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - TRISHNA, LOCATED AT RUP NARAYAN ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - SAGAR DIGHI FAST FOOD CORNER, LOCATED AT MAHARAJA JAGADIPENDRA NARAYAN ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR FUCHKA(PANIPURI), MOMO, PAPRI CHAT AND BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - TAPAN DA&#39;S, LOCATED IN COOCH BEHAR - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;ROTI SABJI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n5 - SAMRAT SWEETS, LOCATED AT RUP NARAYAN ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - SRIKRISHNA MISTANNYA VANDAR, LOCATED AT KADAMTALA - (FAMOUS FOR PARATAS AND ICE CREAM)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n7 - SWASTI SWEETS, LOCATED AT &nbsp;BABURHAT - (FAMOUS FOR JALEBI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>8 - COOCH BEHAR - {FAMOUS FOR MACHHER JHOL IS A STEW MADE FROM FISH, POTATOES, TOMATOES AND SEASONINGS ; SUKTO IS A DISH MADE FROM VEGETABLES}</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(576, 14, 31, 757, 'West Bengal', 'INDIA', 'MALDA (ENGLISH BAZAR)', 'park-bench-385733_640.jpg', 'park-bench-385733_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Also known as English Bazar or Ingraz Bazar locally or sometimes just the Mango City, Malda is a city in the north of the state of West Bengal proximate to other popular tourist destinations like Darjeeling and Siliguri. Malda, or Maldah, is in fact the second largest city in the northern part of West Bengal and the first city to feature a court dedicated to women. It lies on the banks of the Mahananda River which is what Maldah tourism attributes most of its success to. The tropical climate attracts many tourists from across the country and it is most visited while visiting other northern cities in the state like Siliguri and Darjeeling. The Malda Museum is a popular attraction in the city of Malda. The city is also close to cities like Uttar Dinajpur, Dakshin Dinajpur, Murshidabad and Tarapith. The city features many restaurants and eateries that serve local Bengali cuisine and one must not forget to visit as many as possible. This city of Malda used to have an operational airport, for the moment it is in the process of relocation. In the meanwhile Siliguri Airport and another few airstrips like Bagdogra in the vicinity serve Malda. A bunch of Hindu and Muslim festivals are celebrated at Malda including Durga and Kali Pua, Id-ul-Fitr and Christmas. The city is worth visiting during this time and sees a world of change in terms of d&eacute;cor and mood. During the Indian independence movement, Malda was a subject of dispute between India and Pakistan. Maldah is located between two historically important cities Gaur and Pandua. Gaur is home to the famous Firoj Minar Gaur.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Malda Offers a large range of hotels located all over the city, providing varied services and catering to various pocket sizes. Here, plethora of star hotels is available as per the budget. Tourists can thus, choose deluxe or economy hotels of their choice, as per the comfort and convenience.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Malda does not have an airport of its own and its previous airport was closed down due to disturbances with Bangladesh way back in 1972. The nearest airport is the Netaji Subhash Chandra Bose International Airport.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Malda has easy road access. Located on NH 34, Malda is about 350 kms away from Kolkata. If don&rsquo;t want to hire an exclusive cab, then a bus can easily be taken for a nominal rent. North Bengal State transport runs daily buses from nearby places to Malda.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Malda Town is the main railway station, lending Malda excellent connectivity, not just with nearby places like Kolkata, but also Delhi and Mumbai. Trains are pretty regular, but they do not run on a daily basis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - The intercity transport, especially travelling between old Malda and New Malda (English Bazaar), is maintained by city run transport facilities. The rates are fixed by the municipality so need not worry about haggling or being cheated. Also along with autos and rickshaws, intra city bus route is also widespread.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - AAHELI , LOCATED AT RABINDRA AVENUE - (FAMOUS FOR MIXED FRIED RICE AND KADHI PANEER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - BEDWIN, LOCATED IN MALDA - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN ROLL)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - GK RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT ABA GANI KHAN SARANI - (FAMOUS FOR NORTH INDIAN FOOD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - SWAAD, LOCATED AT MALDA - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN FRY AND FISH CUTLETS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - GOURAV, LOCATED AT NETAJI SUBHASH ROAD, NORTH PIROJPUR - (FAMOUS FOR EGG ROLL)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - IDEAL BAKERY, LOCATED AT KRISHNA JIBAN SANYAL ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR CAKES AND PASTRIES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - PABNA SWEETS, LOCATED AT RABINDRA AVENUE - (FAMOUS FOR SANDESH IS A SWEET)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>8 - RADHA RANI SWEET, LOCATED IN MALDA - (FAMOUS FOR DHOKLA AND KACHURI)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(577, 14, 31, 757, 'West Bengal', 'INDIA', 'HALDIA', 'harbor-1574214_640.jpg', 'harbor-1574214_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">A major sea port as well as an industrial belt, Haldia is located in the state of West Bengal which is prominent for its manufacturing and coal industries. It is located near the mouth of the Hooghly River, one of the distributaries of the Ganga.For ages Haldia has been used as a viable sea port for Kolkata, the capital city of West Bengal. Kolkata&rsquo;s waters being too shallow for large ships, owing to silting, forced the state government to develop Haldia. In the process, Haldia has developed into a prosperous industrial town and has attracted several thousand tourists on a yearly basis, both from the business and leisure sects of travellers. There are many interesting places to be visited in Haldia such as Brajanathchak, Brajalalchak, Casurina Coatline, Gopaljew Temple and more. Modernization and the mall culture here, make for a perfect weekend getaway. Perhaps the most popular mall in India, City Centre mall is located in the middle of the residential area of this small town. Casurina Coastline with beautiful plantations against the horizon is a very vibrant picnic spot and many locals flock there on the weekends. Haldia is a perfect getaway from the bustling city of Kolkata, especially given the proximity. The climate in Haldia is divided in three main seasons i.e. summer, winter and the Monsoons.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Haldia has a number of accommodation options across different budget ranges. Most of these offer a number of services and activities and are known to serve some delicious food.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\n<strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest International Airport from Haldia is Netaji Subhash Chandra Airport, Kolkata, roughly four hour drive from Haldia. The Airport is well connected with other major cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Haldia has own its railway station named as Haldia Railway Station. It is well connected to Agra, Howrah, Mumbai and Sealdah.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Haldia is connected to Kolkata via AH 45 and is motor able in around 2 hours. It is about 120 kilometres from the state capital, Kolkata.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - One should be able to find themselves a cab to move about the city conveniently.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - HALDIA - (FAMOUS FOR JHALMURI IS TYPE OF PUFFED RICE MADE FROM LEMON, ONION, CHILI, TOMATO, SALT AND OTHER SPICE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - AALA, LOCATED AT BESIDE CANARA BANK, CITY CENTER ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR BIRYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - PUNJABI DHABA, LOCATED AT NEAR NATIONAL WEIGHBRIDGE - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN BUTTER MASALA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - CHAKHLE HALDIA, LOCATED AT AKASH INN-CIPET RD - (FAMOUS FOR DOSA, CHICKEN MOMO, PAPRI CHAT, CHOWMEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - HANGOUT FOOD COURT, LOCATED AT HALDIA CITY CENTER MALL, NEAR MUNICIPALITY, HIT COLLAGE RD - (FAMOUS FOR CHILLI CHICKEN, CHANA BHATURA, CHICKEN KABAB)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - CALCUTTA SWEETS, LOCATED AT HALDIA - TAMLUK - MECHADA RD, PARAMHANSAPUR - {FAMOUS FOR RASGOLLA, MISTI DAHI/ DOI AND GAJAR(CARROT) KA HALWA}</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(578, 14, 31, 757, 'West Bengal', 'INDIA', 'HOWRAH (HAORA)', 'howrah-1332650_1280.jpg', 'howrah-1332650_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Howrah is situated on the western bank of the Hooghly River in the state of West Bengal. Counted among the popular tourist destinations in the country, it is also considered as the twin city of Kolkata. People visit here to view various attractions like Anand Niketan Kirtishala, Howrah Bridge, Indian Botanical Garden and many others. Indian Botanical Gardens is home to The Great Banyan, one of the major attractions of the tourists who visit this garden. It is one of the oldest gardens of Kolkata region and was built in the year 1786. History of this district dates back to 500 years. The name Howrah was derived from a village named Harirah. Temples of the city attracts the attention of tourist because of their unique architecture. Santragachhi Jheel is another attraction where one can find various species of migratory birds. Among the wide species of birds, whistling duck is the popular one that is found there. October to March is considered as the best time to visit Howrah. However, the district has a tropical type of climate throughout the year. Howrah is connected to Kolkata by four bridges namely Vivekananda, Vidyasagar, the most popular Howrah and Nivedita. A walk along any one of these bridges is amazing and the views one can catch of the river Ganga, the dhows and ships floating in it are breath taking. The better aspect lies in the fact that each of these bridges is unique in their own ways. The Vidyasagar Bridge or setu is a cable stayed bridge which offers grandeur and height whereas the Howrah Bridge with its complicated network design is a cantilever bridge.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">This city has ample of hotels which provide good and comfortable accommodation. &nbsp;The hotels are well equipped with all sort of advanced facilities. One can get luxurious and as well as budget hotels in Howrah offering the tourists a comfortable stay.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Netaji Subhash Chandra Bose International Airport is is the nearest airport to Howrah located at a distance of 50 kms at Kolkata. Regular flights are available from here to the major destinations in and around India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Howrah terminus is connected to the rest of the country and the state via some major scheduled long distance trains. Regular departures to Mumbai and New Delhi are available.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Howrah is connected to the rest of the country and the state via National Highways 6 and 2. It is accessible by road from various closely destinations like Jamshedpur, Siliguri and Darjeeling.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - HOWRAH(HAORA) - {FAMOUS FOR PATISHAPTA PEETHA IS A TYPE OF SWEET PANCAKE STUFFED WITH COCONUT FILLING ; GURER PAYESH IS A DESERT MADE FROM RICE WITH PALM JAGGERY ; &nbsp;DUDH PULI &nbsp;IS A DESERT MADE FROM COCONUT AND DATE PALM JAGGERY AND THE SHELL IS MADE OF RICE FLOUR ; LEDIKENI IS A SWEET MADE FROM CHHENA AND FLOUR AND SOAKED IN SUGAR SYRUP}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - MOGHAL EMPIRE RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT KONA EXPY, CHATTERJIHAT, SHIBPUR, HOWRAH - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN ROLL)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - DAKSHIN, LOCATED AT GRAND TRUNK RD, SALKIA - (FAMOUS FOR CHEESE MASALA DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - VEG ADDA RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT MAULANA ABUL KALAM AZAD RD, BABUDANGA, MALI PANCHGHARA - (FAMOUS FOR CHOWMEIN AND MANCHURIAN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - STREET CAFE(HOWRAH), LOCATED AT 7 HURDUTTA RAI CHAMARIA RD - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;CHEESE SANDWICH)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - FOODIEX RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT KONA EXPY, CHATTERJIHAT, SHIBPUR - (FAMOUS FOR MOOMS AND CHICKEN ROLLS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - AFREEN BIRIYANI HOUSE, LOCATED AT BELILIOUS ROAD, MAIDEN, HOWRAH RAILWAY STATION, KADAM TALA - (FAMOUS FOR MUTTON BRIYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>8 - MISSION CAFE BELUR, LOCATED AT FORUM RANGOLI MALL, 2ND FLOOR, GIRISH GHOSH ROAD, BELUR - (FAMOUS FOR CHOLA BHATURA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>9 - SANJIB&#39;S RESTAURANT,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT S.N.N. GANGULY ROAD, SANTRAGACHI MORE - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN BUTTER MASALA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>10 - PANCH BHOG&#39;S, LOCATED AT RAMESHWAR MALIA LN, HOWRAH RAILWAY STATION, KADAM TALA - (FAMOUS FOR EGG CAKES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>11 - ROLL &#39;N&#39; TANDOOR, LOCATED AT GHULAM HUSSAIN SARDAR LN, SHIBTALA, NAORA, SHIBPUR - (FAMOUS FOR ROLLS AND KABABS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>12 - MOGHAL EMPIRE, LOCATED AT SANTRAGACHI - (FAMOUS FOR EGG CHICKEN ROLL)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>13 - AGARWAL&#39;S, LOCATED AT 82/2, MUKTARAM BABU ST, COLLEGE STREET MARKET, MACHUABAZAR - (FAMOUS FOR PAV BHAJI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>14 - KUSUM ROLLS, LOCATED AT KARNANI MANSION, PARK STREET AREA - (FAMOUS FOR EGG ROLL, EGG CHICKEN ROLL)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>15 - PETER CAT, LOCATED AT 18A, PARK STREET, OPPOSITE KFC, PARK STREET AREA - (FAMOUS FOR KEBAB)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>16 - KEWPIE&#39;S, LOCATED AT ELGIN LANE, OFF HEYSHAM ROAD, BEHIND NETAJI BHAVAN - (FAMOUS FOR DAAB CHINGRI IS A TYPE OF CURRY MADE FROM &nbsp;PRAWNS AND COCONUT)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>17 - KALIGODAM SWEETS, LOCATED AT 511, GRAND TRUNK RD, VIVEK VIHAR, CHOURA BUSTEE, SHIBPU - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>18 - TIWARI SWEET, LOCATED AT BELUR, LILUAH - (FAMOUS FOR RASGULLA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n19 - PARASHURAM, LOCATED AT GRAND TRUNK ROAD SOUTH, HOWRAH RAILWAY STATION, KADAM TALA - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;KULFI, GULAB JAMUN, LADDU)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>20 - KASTURI SWEETS &amp; SNACKS, LOCATED AT BHAGABAN CHATTERJEE LN, KADAMTALA, BANTRA, ICHAPUR - {FAMOUS FOR CHOWMEIN SINGARA(SAMOSA)}</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(579, 14, 31, 757, 'West Bengal', 'INDIA', 'JALPAIGURI', 'elephant-399305_1280.jpg', 'elephant-399305_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Jalpai in Hindi means Olive, which were found all over Jalpaiguri in the early 1900s. &nbsp;Jalpaiguri district shares international borders with Bhutan in the North and Bangladesh in the East. The Darjeeling hills are proximate to Jalpaiguri and make for an ideal day trip from here. Apart from this, Jalpaiguri Tourism also attracts onward tourists from Siliguri and other Northern towns of West Bengal. Popular attractions include Jubilee Park, the Town Club Stadium and the famous River Teesta. For children, the Teesta Park along the banks of the river Karala is an ideal place. The Jalpesh temple is located around 15 kilometres from the town and there is also a famous Shiva temple in the region. There is also a National Park, which is around 80 kilometres from the town. It is a famous tourist place particularly known for the number of tea gardens, rice farms and heavy downpour. While being a beautiful tourist destination, it is comparatively less crowded and undisturbed in nature. Jalpaiguri has tea gardens as far as your sight goes, rice plantations, hills covered with lush green bushes, breathtaking landscape and a small, closed town to discover. It is not only an important place in West Bengal but also important to the whole country because it connects the North East India to the rest of the country. Topographically, this district of West Bengal is criss-crossed by rivers, rivulets and hills. Hence, Jalpaiguri is a heavenly abode to the travellers who love nature.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The strategic location of Jalpaiguri as a gateway to the north east and its immense tourist potential has led to the rise of a number of accommodations in Jalpaiguri district. Many of these are strategically placed within the town while others share proximity to the scenic spots which tourists come to view. There are a number of star hotels in Jalpaiguri which provide travellers with a high level of luxury in its accommodation, dining as well as entertainment services. With spacious and stylish lobbies, these star hotels have comfortable suites which are both clean and comfortable.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Bagdogra airport is the nearest to Jalpaiguri. It is a small domestic airport with flights running from the major cities of the country. Just 20 kms from the town, taxies and buses are available from Bagdogra to Jalpaiguri.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Extremely well connected by road to the nearby cities state tourism buses run at regular intervals to and from the state along with private buses increasing connectivity.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The New Jalpaiguri Railway station is just 4 kms away from the town it is one of the biggest railway stations in the city and is well connected to nearby cities as well as key cities of the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Travellers can use buses and shared rickshaw for travelling from one destination to the other. Since Jalpaiguri is a small town and attractions are nearby, travellers can also travel on foot from one place to another.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - JALPAIGURI - (FAMOUS FOR PATI SHAPTA IS A TYPE OF PANCAKE MADE FROM RICE FLOUR AND STUFFED WITH SWEETENED COCONUT, DATE JIGGERY AND MILK)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - SARTAJ RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT WARD 6, SILIGURI - (FAMOUS FOR KABAB)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - ROYAL SAGAR,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT DBC ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN BIRYANI, MOMO, BURGER, DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 &nbsp;- AVINANDAN FOODIES CORNER PROP TAMAL DAS, LOCATED AT BEGUNTARY MORE, BESIDE OF JALPAIGURI LAW COLLEGE - (FAMOUS FOR EGG CHICKEN MOGHLAI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - MISTI MUKH SWEET SHOP, LOCATED AT HALDIBARI ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR RASOGOLLA, SANDESH, MALAI CHAMCHAM, RAS KADAM)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n6 - LADDOO GOPAL - PURE VEG, LOCATED AT 1ST FLOOR, JEEVANDEEP BUILDING, RASHTRIYA GHAIPATHA, WARD 42, SALUGARA, SILIGURI - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;MUNG DAL KA HALWA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - GURU SWEETS AND SNACKS, LOCATED AT OPPOSITE VISHAL CINEMA HALL SEVOKE ROAD, SILIGURI - (FAMOUS FOR DESI GHEE LADDUS AND &nbsp;RAS MALAI)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(580, 14, 31, 757, 'West Bengal', 'INDIA', 'KHARAGPUR', 'sea-1801749_6401.jpg', 'sea-1801749_6402.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Known for its long railway platform, the third longest in the country, Kharagpur for ages have been a premier education centre in India and houses the famous Indian Institute of Technology&rsquo;s Kharagpur campus. Kharagpur, for long, has been known as India&rsquo;s largest railway settlement with over 13000 employees inhabiting here. The huge Kharagpur Lake in the city has been a popular place of tourist interest for years and the city&rsquo;s youth liven up the place even more. Kharagpur, owing to its educational influence has always portrayed itself as a city, full of zest, vigour and enthusiasm. Kharagpur is one of those places in India that is known for its Hindu Muslim unity. Both the communities have lived together here for ages. The Kali Temple and the Shahi Masjid, both of which are popular religious tourist destinations bear a proof to this fact. By popular demand, with students at the epicentre in no small part, Kharagpur is known for serving some of the best food in the region. The city is strewn with road side joints and restaurants that serve delicious Bengali food and other cuisines. For some cheap, unique shopping tourists can head over to Puratan, Gole or Gate bazaars. From an educational town to a city that offers true tourist value, Kharagpur tourism seems to have done a good job. Being within driving distance of Kolkata and some cities in neighbouring states, Kharagpur is easily accessible. Winters are the exact time when one should visit Kharagpur.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The city of Kharagpur is home to numerous reputed guest houses, hotels and lodges that offer a variety of services to the visitors and make their stay a contented and pleasant one. From modest budget hotels to luxurious ones for the elite customers, there are a variety of choices available for the visitors to choose from, depending upon their budget and preferences.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Kharagpur is served by Kolkata&rsquo;s Netaji Subhash Chandra International airport with connections to the rest of the country and the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Kharagpur Railway station with the third longest platform in the country is one of the major lines in the country and connects to Delhi, Mumbai and Kolkata directly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - National Highway 6 connects Kharagpur to the state capital Kolkata and is approximately 131 kilometres from it. Kharagpur is a 2 hours drive from Kolkata.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Cars, auto rickshaws, tourist cars and buses and private vehicles form the major means of communication within this city. Share auto facilities are also available for those looking forward to travelling at lower fares. Private travel agencies offer bus and taxi services for sight-seeing and commuting within and around this city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1- LITTLE SISTER BAKERY,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT NEAR PURI GATE, CHOTA TENGRA, WEST MIDNAPORE - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN PUFF AND PATTIES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - TAAZ BIRYANI, LOCATED AT NEW BUS STAND - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN TIKKA OR CHICKEN TANDOORI AND KEBAB WITH SALAD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - SUPER DUPER, LOCATED AT IIT KHARAGPUR - (FAMOUS FOR SOUTH INDIAN FOOD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - JCB CANTEEN, LOCATED AT SCHOLAR AVE, IIT KHARAGPUR - (FAMOUS FOR EGG FRIED RICE, CHEESE OMELET)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - ASHIM CANTEEN, LOCATED AT NEHRU HALL GARDEN, IIT KHARAGPUR&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;- (FAMOUS FOR CHOCOLATE SHAKES AND SANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - SAHARA RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT IIT KHARAGPUR - (FAMOUS FOR VEG BIRYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - SASMAL FAST FOOD, LOCATED AT HIJLI CO OPERATIVE SOCIETY, PREMBAZAR&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;- (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN POKORA AND CUTLET)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>8 - TIKKA, LOCATED IN IIT KHARAGPUR &nbsp;- (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN TIKKA, SAMOSAS AND MASALA DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>9 - RADHAKANTA, LOCATED AT 39, EAST AVE, RANGAMATI, MEDINIPUR - (FAMOUS FOR CHEENE KA RASAGULLA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>10 - MISTI MAHAL, LOCATED AT RABINDRA NAGAR, MEDINIPUR - (FAMOUS FOR SHAWARMA ROLLS FILLED WITH CHICKEN KEBABS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n11 - KAKA SWEETS, LOCATED AT BIDHAN NAGAR EAST, MEDINIPUR - (FAMOUS FOR CHAAT ITEMS)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(581, 14, 31, 757, 'West Bengal', 'INDIA', 'KRISHNANAGAR', 'bat-672816_12802.jpg', 'bat-672816_12803.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Traditions of yore, art and architecture Krishnanagar is a historical town in West Bengal with a legacy worth exploring and discovering. Situated on the banks of the river Jalangi and only 132 kms from the state capital Kolkata Krishnanagar boasts of a sublime heritage and an inimitable vintage appeal. Locally known as Khore, the place was named after its ruler Raja Krishna Chandra Rai, who was a great patron of art and architecture. Evidently, the place offers an insight into a rich cultural and artistic tradition, one that attracts tourists for its distinctive appeal, clay modelling and religious festivals. With the climatic conditions in the town being primarily moderate, tourists can visit throughout the year. Krishnanagar is an important centre for culture and literature. The local population of the city continues to engage in a vibrant culture of literary exchange. But what upholds the cultural sanctity of the town is a sub urban locality called Ghurni. Here, one can find a colony of artists creating wonders in clay. Besides the popular deity images it features clay models of human figures, fruits and animals that are meticulously worked out in an array of open studios. Breeding a rare tradition in clay modelling, Krishnanagar has given one of the major art forms to Bengal. The Rajbari also known as the Krishnanagar Palace is by far the most widely visited architectural marvel in the city and is mostly visited for the celebration of different festivals. The best time to visit Krishnagar is in the winters.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are some deluxe and medium to budget accommodation options in Krishnanagar.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The Kolkata International airport is the best destination to reach. One can take a taxi from there to Krishnanagar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - There is no railway station in Krishnanagar. Local EMU trains are the most convenient option to reach Kolkata and one can opt for a taxi from there to Krishnanagar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Located on National Highway 34, Krishnanagar is connected with Nabadwip through Krishnagar Route No. 8.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- West Bengal state buses are well connecting all parts of the state with Kolkata. Deluxe and A/C luxury buses are available from Kolkata to various cities in the state and neighbouring states.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - HOT LIPS, LOCATED AT SH 11 - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN TANDOORI)&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - AROMA RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT SH 11 - (FAMOUS FOR CHAUMEEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - FOOD HEAVEN, LOCATED AT ANANTA HARI MITRA ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR BIRYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - RED CHILLI, LOCATED AT 1, D. L. SADAR HOSPITAL, DL ROY ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR MOGLAI PARANTHA AND EGG ROLL)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - NAYAN&#39;S GANGTOK, LOCATED AT &nbsp;SH 11 - (FAMOUS FOR MOMOS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - TASTI, LOCATED AT 28, RN TAGORE ROAD&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;- (FAMOUS FOR DALPURI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - GOVINDA&#39;S RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT MAYAPUR - (FAMOUS FOR SOUTH INDIAN FOODS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>8 - KRISHNANAGAR - {FAMOUS FOR SHORBHAJA IS A SWEET CAKE MADE OF MILK CREAM(SHOR), SUGAR SYRUP, KHOYA AND CHENNA ARE ALSO MIXED}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '');
