(582, 14, 31, 757, 'West Bengal', 'INDIA', 'PURULIA', 'landscape-393422_640.jpg', 'landscape-393422_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The western most districts in the state of West Bengal, Purulia is a beautiful destination blessed with mesmerizing natural beauty. Purulia is slowly becoming a popular tourist spot amongst national tourists the township is well connected with the rest of the country and gifts a breakaway from the monotonous routines of the day to day city lives. Purulia a town close to the western border of West Bengal is one of those places which are situated in the middle of a lush greenery flanked with waterfalls and natural unadulterated wildlife. The Kasagbati and Panchet water reservoirs serve Purulia&rsquo;s water requirements and also make for a photographer&rsquo;s paradise. Saheb Bandh is another small water reservoir where one can go boating and fishing. Purulia&rsquo;s bird population includes the Pakhi Pahar, which translates to Bird of the Hills. These birds are attracted to rocks on the hillside from which the name of the hill is derived. Deer park at Purulia close to the Kangsabati dam and the Ajodhya hills are two of the many tourist spots that add to the success of Purulia tourism. The town&rsquo;s landscape is picture perfect and has had an influence on an Australian company that markets designer homes under the name Purulia. Festivities are at their best during Durga and Kali Puja at Purulia. Diwali sees the entire city decorated and painted with different hues. The Santhal Tribe celebrates their festival, Bandhna, which involves dance, music and meat based feasts. Sometimes, the locals also indulge themselves with country liquor called Hadia. The best time to visit Purulia is in the winters.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Purulia is a popular eco tourism spot apart from being a regular tourism destination. There are all kinds of accommodation available for a tourist, depending on their budget, nature of stay, preference of services, location and duration. The reservation to the government rest houses open well in advance, find out all the necessary details online.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Netaji Subhash Chandra Bose airport in Kolkata is the nearest airport to Purulia. The airport is well connected to all parts of India and abroad. Purulia is 330 kms from Kolkata and the journey hereon can be completed by railway or roadway both.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Being a popular tourist spot, Purulia is well connected by road to other nearby cities in the state of West Bengal. Regular government and private buses along with taxies and cabs run to and from the township maintaining its connectivity.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - 1.5 kms away from the main town, Purulia railway station is known for being the best in the region. It is a junction here and most trains on long route stop here. Purulia has direct trains from major cities and connecting trains from Kolkata and Howrah. The connecting train from Howrah which runs to Purulia runs on all days except for Saturday.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Purulia being a small town in West Bengal has basic facilities including rickshaws and taxis for commuting in this area.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - MADHURI SNACKS BAR, LOCATED IN PURULIA - (FAMOUS FOR DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - FLAVOURS THE FAMILY RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT BARAKAR ROAD, CHAPARI - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN CHILLY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - DULAL SWEETS, LOCATED AT RANCHI ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORI SABJI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - BALIKA SWEETS, LOCATED &nbsp;IN PURULIA - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - TRIPTI, &nbsp;LOCATED AT B.T. SARKAR ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR CHILLI CHICKEN AND CHICKEN ROLL)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - MONDIRA SNACKS, LOCATED AT POST OFFICE - (FAMOUS FOR ROLLS AND NOODLES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(583, 14, 31, 757, 'West Bengal', 'INDIA', 'SERAMPORE', 'simpolo-2020169_640.jpg', 'simpolo-2020169_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Serampore is a city and a municipality in Hooghly district in the Indian state of West Bengal. It is a part of the area covered by Kolkata Metropolitan Development Authority. It is a pre-colonial town on the right bank of the Hooghly River. It was part of Danish India under the name Frederiksnagore from 1755 to 1845. Serampore is one of the oldest colonial cities of India at the banks of Hooghly River. It is the home of arguably the most ancient Jagannath Temple of the world. The Jagannath temple of Mahesh is dated back to 1755. The great Serampore Trio has started to build a modern Serampore in 18th Century and that ignited a revolution that helped our Modern Bengal. The Serampore College was built by them which still hold its ground strong. Situated 25 kms north of Kolkata, Serampore is a pre-colonial town lying across the bank of Hooghly River. It used to be the major trading centre during Danish India, before British East India Company acquired the Denmark&rsquo;s holdings in India in 1845. Enjoy the breathtaking view of river from the tall clock tower of the crumbling Imambara, a classical mosque built in 1861 as a learning and worship hub.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>There are some deluxe and medium to budget accommodation options nearby Serampore.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Netaji Subhash Chandra Bose International Airport is 17 kms away from the heart of Kolkata which is located at Dumdum. This airport is well connected to all major cities in India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Howrah, Bidhan Nagar and Sealdah are major railway stations in Kolkata. These stations are well connected to all cities in India. Metro rail system in Kolkata connects all the main junctions in Kolkata. It is a good way to reach the different parts of the city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Roads are well connected in Kolkata, so one can easily go through by its own car. One can also hire taxi also.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Kolkata bus services is very frequent most of the time West Bengal state buses connect all parts Kolkata. Deluxe buses are available from Kolkata to various cities in the states.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1- OM CASUAL DINING RESTRAURANT, LOCATED AT 63, NS AVE - (FAMOUS FOR CHILI CHICKEN AND GARLIC SOUP)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - RUPASHI RESTAURANT, &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT ABOVE DOMINO&#39;S PIZZA, GRAND TRUNK ROAD, MANIKTALA - (FAMOUS FOR MUTTON BIRYANI,CHICKEN TIKKA MASALA,CHICKEN RESHMI KEBAB)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - NABANNA HOTEL &amp; RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT &nbsp;81,N.S.AVENUE - (FAMOUS FOR BIRIYANI AND &nbsp;CHOWMIN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - REDA RIGHTTASTE, LOCATED AT 109, N.S. AVE. HOOGHLY - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN BIRYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - BAWARCHI, LOCATED AT SWEETY PLAZA , N S AVENUE, RAJENDRA BAG ROAD&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;- (FAMOUS FOR KEBAB)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n6 - NEW HAJI, LOCATED AT A/1/8, G.T. ROAD, BELTING BAZAR - (FAMOUS FOR MUTTON BIRYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - NEW EVEREST RESTAURANT, LOCATED IN SERAMPORE - (FAMOUS FOR MOGLAI PAROTA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n8 - BASANTI CABIN, LOCATED AT KM SHAH STREET - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN CUTLET)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>9 - BUNTY, LOCATED AT BP DEY STREET - (FAMOUS FOR MOMOS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>10 - MAHESH CHANDRA DUTTA MISTANNA BHANDAR, LOCATED AT 7/A, THAKURDAS BABU LANE - (FAMOUS FOR GULAB JAMUN AND SONDESH)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>11 - SATYANARAYAN FAST FOOD, LOCATED AT &nbsp;A 156, NS AVENUE - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN SAMSOSA, EGG ROLLS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>12 - ANNAPURNA SWEETS, LOCATED AT SHYAMACHARAN DEY STREET, KHASH BAGAN - (FAMOUS FOR MISTI DOI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>13 - MA TARA SWEETS, LOCATED AT BARABAGAN, SERAMPORE, DAKSHIN RAJYADHARPUR&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;- (FAMOUS FOR ROSOGULLA AND KACHORI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>14 - UMA SWEETS &amp; SNACKS, LOCATED AT GRAND TRUNK RD, NEHRU NAGAR COLONY, MAHESH BOSE PARA - (FAMOUS FOR JALEBI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>15 - SHREE DURGA MISTANNA BHANDAR, LOCATED AT NS AVE. - (FAMOUS FOR KULFI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>16 - JOGESHWAR MISTANNA BHANDAR, LOCATED AT GURUDAS BHATTACHARYA LN., DAKSHIN RAJYADHARPUR - {FAMOUS FOR ROSOGOLLA AND SINGARA (SAMOSAS)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>17 - BINA SWEET, LOCATED AT 75, KARL MARX SARANI, SUBHASH NAGAR 2, RISHRA - (FAMOUS FOR KALAKAND AND PANTUA IS A SWEET MADE FROM SEMOLINA, KHOYA, MILK, GHEE AND SUGAR)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>18 - SWEET HOME, LOCATED AT GURUDWARA, BAKAR MAHAL, 7, BAZAZ BARRACKPORE, SADAR BAZAR - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA &nbsp;AND JELABI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>19 - ADI SATYANARAYAN MISTANNA BHANDAR, LOCATED AT ADI SATYANARAYAN MISTANNA BHANDAR&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;- (FAMOUS FOR KAJU SANDESH IS A SWEET)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>20 - MRITUNJOY AND GRANDSON, LOCATED AT &nbsp;G.T. ROAD, NEAR BAIDYABATI RAIL GATE, NEMAI TIRTHA ROAD, BAIDYAPARA - (FAMOUS FOR CHAMCHAM AND RASOGOLLA)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(584, 14, 31, 757, 'West Bengal', 'INDIA', 'ALIPORE (SOUTH PARGANAS)', 'bird-1038316_6402.jpg', 'bird-1038316_6403.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Alipore is a place that is situated in the South Parganas district of the state of West Bengal. It is an important locality that is situated near the city of Kolkata. Alipore is an old place and there are few historical places that one can visit here. Alipore is well known for its large mansions and well maintained gardens. The Alipore Zoological Gardens are among the oldest menageries in the state and the place is home to several species of animals such as elephants, Bengal tigers, rhinoceros, jaguars, camels, zebras, emus, giraffes and African lions. The zoo also has a wide collection of birds. The place is famous for the Bengali handicrafts that are made here. These can be purchased as souvenirs. It is also worth visiting the Alipore Library. This is an old place and has an excellent collection of books. The Parasnath Temple is a Jain temple and it is a beautiful building and a must see place, while travelling to the region.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Tourists will get some suitable Hotels, accommodations and restaurants around Alipore.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Subhash Chandra Bose International Airport locally called as Dumdum Airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- New Alipur or Majherhat Railway station on Budge railway zone.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Metro</strong> - Jatin Das Park Railway Station. Tourists can hire a taxi or travel by bus to reach Alipore from these stations.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - KRISHNA SNACKS BAR,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT 45, BANKIM MUKHERJEE SARANI, BLOCK D - (FAMOUS FOR CHEESE ONION CHILLI TOMATO CAPSICUM RAVA DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - MANGIO, LOCATED AT 17/1F, ALIPORE RD - (FAMOUS FOR PASTRIES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - RED CLUB, LOCATED AT NO.17/1F, 4TH FLOOR, THE ENCLAVE - (FAMOUS FOR COCONUT ICECREAM AND &nbsp;FISH TIKKA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - ZYKA, LOCATED AT BLOCK P, 850, NEW ALIPORE RD, AJOY NAGAR, BUROSHIBTALLA - (FAMOUS FOR CHILLY MUSHROOM, POTATO DAL MAHHANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - SNACK STREET, LOCATED AT 17/1D, ALIPORE ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - KHIDKI-CHAAT CENTRE, LOCATED AT HUMAYUN KABIR SARANI, BLOCK G - (FAMOUS FOR BHEL PURI AND BATATA VADA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - GARDEN CAFE, LOCATED AT 8/1, ALIPORE ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;DAHI BADA, BUTTER MASALA DOSA, SAMBAR, CHUTNEY AND VADAS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>8 - SUPER SNACK BAR, LOCATED AT 513 A, NEW ALIPORE ROAD, BLOCK M - (FAMOUS FOR PAY BHAJI, CHANA BHATURA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>9 - PAM&#39;S CAFE, LOCATED AT 31, RAMTANU LAHIRI SARANI, BLOCK D, NEW ALIPORE - (FAMOUS FOR CHOCOLATE SHAKE AND MANGO SHAKE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>10 - DRIVE-IN, LOCATED AT NO.1 ALIPORE ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR KULCHA IS A TYPE OF FLATBREAD MADE FROM WHEAT FLOUR AND EATEN WITH CHOLE AND PANEER TIKKA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>11 - BAWARCHI(CHETLA), LOCATED AT 17A, JAINUDDIN MISTRY LANE, ALIPUR, CHETLA - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;EGG-ROLL)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n12 - ANAMIKA, LOCATED AT SAHAPUR - (FAMOUS FOR EGGS ROLLS, ONION ROLLS AND PANEER ROLLS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>13 - DROP-IN, LOCATED AT 57, DIAMOND HARBOUR ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR PANNER TIKKA BUTTER MASALA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>14 - JAI JAWAN STALL, LOCATED AT TARATALA ROAD, OPPOSITE C.E.S.C - (FAMOUS FOR EGG CHICKEN ROLL)<