HA, BHOWANIPORE - (FAMOUS FOR PAROTA WITH EGG FRY WITH ONIONS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>26 - JUST FRIES, LOCATED AT 43 DPS ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR FRIED MOMO, FRENCH FRIES, FISH CUTLET)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>27 - FLURY&#39;S, LOCATED AT 8 B, ALIPORE TOWER ALIPORE ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN PATTY, CHOCOLATE CUBES AND &nbsp;COLD COFFEE)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(585, 14, 31, 745, 'Maharashtra', 'INDIA', 'AURANGABAD', 'jowar-223591_640.jpg', 'jowar-223591_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Aurangabad is one of the 38 districts in Bihar, with a city of the same name. The beautiful city boasts of a unique culture and identity. The Magadhi speaking people that are settled here have largely taken up agriculture and related activities as their occupation. Aurangabad city offers a host of tourist attractions to its visitors, ranging from historical places to temples. It boasts of a vibrant history and holds the distinction of being a part of one of the largest and strongest empires in ancient India Magadha. The region of Magadha comprised of a vast empire in the ancient period, dating from 600 to 250 BC. Aurangabad was also ruled by Bimbisar and Ajatshatru. Later on, Chandragupta Maurya and Ashoka ruled the region. After a period, Rajputana came here to settle down. All these rulers have left their mark on the city. Previously a part of the Gaya district, Aurangabad is now an independent district of Bihar. He encouraged the cause of freedom in Bihar and also led the Satyagraha movement in the state. Another significant place in the district is Obra a small town located 16 kms away from Aurangabad city. Obra is well known for the production of Kaleen. The tradition of weaving beautiful and unique carpets in the town dates back to 15th century. Set up near Koriepur village, the Kaleen Udyog is currently managed by the state government. Then, there is Burha, 3 kms to the east of Aurangabad, a location known for a number of historical sites in which Chaityas and large Viharas once stood.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Aurangabad offers good accommodation facilities for an economical price. Tourists get to find premium budget hotels with amenities best fitting their budgets. Most of the hotels allocate dedicated rooms to those who book early. Luxury resorts also help tourists in having a gala time in the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air</strong> - Aurangabad does not have an airport of its own. Closest airport to Aurangabad is Gaya Airport from where flights are available to every city of India. Private taxis are available from the airport to Aurangabad.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Train</strong> - Sasaram is the closest railway station to Aurangabad. It is distanced by 46 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Road</strong> - Aurangabad enjoys decent roads by virtue of the national Highways. Buses and rickshaws serve the city well. It is easily accessible from Gaya, Bhojpur and Patna.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Bus</strong> - One can choose several Maharashtra State Road Transport Corporation (MSRTC) or Private Buses that ply between all other major cities of the state and neighbouring states.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(586, 14, 31, 734, 'Bihar', 'INDIA', 'BANKA', 'banka-720390_1280.jpg', 'banka-720390_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Banka a part of Bhagalpur division is located nearly 231 kms from state capital Patna towards west. Established in February, 1991 Banka is a small quaint little town with lots of natural beauty and greenery spread all around. Literally Banka means brave in Hindi and is located between two rivers Chandan and Orhani. It also forms the border of Bihar &amp; Jharkhand State and is known for its religious places, the most famous being the Durga Mandir in Karharia. Every year hundreds of devotees come to Banka to offer prayers at this temple. Banka is considered as an agrarian economy with the city being also called as the Rice Bowl of Bihar. Though the History of Banka might not date back to hundreds of years but it has an interesting connection to the freedom struggle with the district producing some very famous personalities. The great revolutionary Satish Prasad Jha who was one of the 7 martyrs who hoisted the Indian Flag on Patna Secretariat building on 11th August 1942 belonged to Banka district. Chanan forms the main river of the district, and irrigates a large part of land in Banka district. Other rivers like Belharni and Barua flow in the north western parts of Banka while Chanan &amp; Orhni pass through the middle of the district. Banka district boosts of a rich Flora &amp; Fauna with most of the area having dense forests, falling under the Bounsi Katoriya forest ranges. One can find Tasar worms being reared on Asan trees here. Banka district in Bihar has a rich culture and is famous for its handicrafts &amp; hand looms like the homemade Khadi and Silk. Banka district in Bihar is famous for its religious tourism, having many places which are of religious importance.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are several private lodges and government owned inspection bungalows where rooms are available at affordable rates.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><br />\r\n<strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport is at Ranchi from where to and fro flights are available to all major cities like Delhi, Kolkata, Patna or Mumbai.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train </strong>- The main Railway Station is Banka Railway Station and has many trains passing through thus connecting Banka by rail to other cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - G.T. Road connects the area to other nearby towns. One can also take a bus route via Jamtara when coming from West Bengal side.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Local Transport</strong> - To travel within the district autos, tempos and rickshaws are available easily.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - BANKA &nbsp;- (FAMOUS FOR PANTUA IS A SWEET &nbsp;MADE FROM SEMOLINA, MILK, GHEE AND SUGAR SYRUP)<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(587, 14, 31, 734, 'Bihar', 'INDIA', 'BEGUSARAI', 'bird-326161_640.jpg', 'bird-326161_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Begusarai is a city as well as a municipal council located in Begusarai district existing in the state of Bihar. The city is situated at an average elevation of 41 mts above sea level. It is spread across an area of 1879 sq kms and consists of Asia&#39;s largest oxbow lake, which is known as Kabar Taal containing some of rare and endangered birds located near Manjhaul village. Begusarai derives its name from Begum meaning queen Sarai meaning inn. This is because of the fact that Begum of Bhagalpur used to visit the Simaria Ghat for a month of pilgrimage that later got transformed into the slang form of Begusarai. Begusarai is a district city administrative headquarters on the northern bank of river Ganga. Begusarai is referred to as the Industrial capital of Bihar and is also known as second capital of Bihar. The city has potential for agro- based industries because of large production of maize and oilseeds, etc. &nbsp;Begusarai is a city in the state of Bihar and serves as the administrative headquarters of the district. Begusarai is located on the northern bank of the Holy Ganges River. Begusarai Tourism has promising tourist destinations of its own that can delight easily. The Kanwar Lake Bird Sanctuary and Naula Garh are the prime attractions of Begusarai tourism. The best months to visit the city are from October to March, before the heat sets in. The origins of the name of the city are truly unique. Apparently, the name comes from the synthesis of the words Begum meaning queen and sarai meaning inn. It is believed that the Begum of Bhagalpur visited the Simaria Ghat a place of worship along the banks of Ganga for the duration of one month. Overtime, the place began to be identified as the queen&rsquo;s retreat, thus Begusarai.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Begusarai is the city where perfect accommodation facilities are provided even in the budget hotels. Tourists can look for luxury amenities in certain 3 start hotels as well. It is better to book hotels before beginning the journey to avoid last minute travails.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Lok Nayak Jayaprakash International Airport in Patna is the nearest airport to reach Begusarai. There is a small aerodrome in Ulao, which is 5 kms from Begusarai that can serve as another alternative.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Barauni Railway Junction holds huge importance in east central Bihar. New Delhi Guwahati railway line passes through Begusarai. Several important trains start from this station towards major cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- The nearest bus stop is the located in the heart of Begusarai, which can be reached after travelling a distance of just 1.2 kms. BSRTC buses ply on a regular basis to take you to and from Begusarai.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- The National Highways 28 and 31 connect Begusarai to the different parts of the country. State roads have a complete length of 262 kms.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - BEGUSARAI - {FAMOUS FOR DHUSKA IS A SNACK MADE FROM &nbsp;RICE AND CHANA DAL WITH GREEN CHILLIS AND GARLIC AND THEN FRIED ; PANTUA IS A SWEET MADE FROM SEMOLINA, KHOYA, MILK, GHEE AND SUGAR}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - RAJESH MISHTHAN BHANDAR, LOCATED AT JAIL ROAD, NEAR SARVJANIK DURGA MANDIR, BISHNUPUR - (FAMOUS FOR MAKUNI (STUFFED SATTU PARATHA) IS A SNACK MADE FROM WHEAT FLOUR)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - GOKUL CHAAT HOUSE, LOCATED AT KACHAHARI RD, VISHNUPUR, CHITRAGUPTA NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - CHILLOUT, LOCATED AT GROUND FLOOR, HOTEL PARK INN BUILDING, GD COLLEGE ROAD, BEGUSARAI - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;CAKES AND ICE CREAMS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - MADHUBAN, LOCATED AT KARPURI ROAD, SARVODAYA NAGAR - {FAMOUS FOR BUTTERMILK (LASSI)}</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(588, 14, 31, 734, 'Bihar', 'INDIA', 'BUXAR', 'bullock-cart-331254_640.jpg', 'bullock-cart-331254_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Buxar, a city of Bihar, is one of the most important areas of Buxar district. Located in the state of Bihar, Buxar is a much sought after tourist destination in the region. Located beautifully on the banks of the Holy Ganges, this ancient town is of great historical importance. The name Buxar is said to be derived from Vyaghra-Sar a Sanskrit word meaning tiger and tank respectively. According to popular folklore, sage Rishi Durvasha cursed Rishi Vedshira to a tiger face. Rishi Vedshira&rsquo;s face was restored after he bathed in a holy tank. This holy tank was named VyaghraSar. This seems to suggest a pond that was visited by a tiger to drink water. This is the generally accepted origin of the name of the town. Buxar city guide is incomplete without a mention of the Chausagarh, Buxar Fort, Katkauli ka Maidan as well as for many adventure sports options like kayaking and water sports. It has various beautiful locations such as Dumraon sub sivision and Buxar Sadar of the old Bhojpur district. Two important battles were fought in Buxar. The first of the battles was fought between Humayun and Sher Shah Suri at Chousa in 1539 AD. The battle was won by Sher Shah Suri. Then in Oct 1764, Mir Kasim with his army was defeated Major Hector Monro. The battle ground of Katkauli is 6 kms from the city of Buxar. The stone memorial at Katkauli stands testament to the battle even today. The city of Buxar, like most of Northern India, enjoys a moderate climate. The months of May and June are the hottest while those of December and January are the coldest. It receives most of its rainfall during the monsoon season of July to August.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Buxar offers good affordable accommodation facilities at nominal prices. Tourists can get to find premium amenities best fitting their budgets. Most of the hotels allocate dedicated rooms to those who book early. Luxury resorts also help tourists in having a gala time in the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>By Air - Lok Nayak Jayaprakash International Airport about 110 kms in Patna is the nearest airport to reach Buxar. Metered taxis are available from the airport to take you to Buxar city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>By Train - Buxar has its own railway station. It links with the Howrah Patna New Delhi main line. Metered taxis, Govt. and private buses are available to take visitors to various parts of the Town.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>By Bus - Buxar Bus Stand about 1.5 kms can be easily accessed by tourists because regular bus services from BSRTC are available for traveller&rsquo;s convenience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>By Road - Buxar has got very good road with brick bridges from Koilwar. There are some other good roads such as the great road to Buxar, the Varanasi Road to Sasaram. It is well linked with NH 8 and NH 222.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - BUXAR - [FAMOUS FOR THEKUA IS SWEET DISH MADE FROM WHEAT FLOUR, SUGAR SYRUP OR JAGGERY, GHEE, CARDAMOM ; ANARSA IS A PASTRY SNACK PREPARED FROM POWERED RICE, JAGGERY OR SUGAR ;TILKUT IS A SWEET MADE FROM SEASAME SEEDS AND JAGGERY OR SUGAR]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(589, 14, 31, 734, 'Bihar', 'INDIA', 'CHAPRA', 'plumeria-238689_640.jpg', 'plumeria-238689_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Chhapra is a city and headquarters of the Saran district in the Indian state of Bihar. Also known as Chapra, it is situated near the junction of the Ghaghara River and the Ganges River. Chhapra grew in importance as a river mart in the 18th century when the Dutch, French, Portuguese, and English established saltpetre refineries there. It was recognized as a municipality in 1864. The town has major rail and road connections with the rest of India. A beautiful city is uniquely located at the confluence of the Ganga and Ghagra rivers. Chhapra is a place that finds mention in the books from the ancient to the modern times. Excavations in and around Chhapra have revealed artefacts from the Stone Age thus pointing to the city&rsquo;s rich history. For those looking for good tourist places Chapra has plenty to offer. Not only are there a number of parks and bazaars in the town itself, there are many scenic and historical spots at short excursions. Tourists will find many areas that boast of a rich history and culture. Chhapra has a rich cultural heritage. The city is steeped in history and much to show in terms of Bhojpuri culture of Bihar. People of different religions and communities live together in peace and harmony practicing their own cultures. The languages spoken by well educated people include Hindi and Bhojpuri.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Quality accommodation is available in Chhapra. Staying in luxury hotels will save money with good amenities offered at economical rates. Tourists can enjoy a good stay in the budget hotels that are known to offer best facilities with the best hospitality standards.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Chhapra Junction is the main railway station which connects Chhapra to all major cities of India. The good part about rail travel is that there are a number of options available in terms of trains from Chhapra to distant villages and towns.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Chhapra is about 85 kms away from state capital Patna connected through NH 19. The city is also connected to the neighbouring state of Uttar Pradesh both NH 28A and 28B. Chhapra is well connected with major cities of Bihar, Jharkhand and West Bengal via road service.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - There is much private bus service which provides regular bus service to all major cities as well as rural areas. The BSRTC provides one of the main sources of transport on the road. Apart from it, there are several private transport services a swell that cater to the needs of the people.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- If one wants to visit Chhapra by air, one would have to fly to Loknayak Jai Prakash Narayan airport at Patna in Bihar. There are flights to Patna from all the major towns and cities of the country.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Local Transport </strong>- It is relatively easy to travel around the city due to the present of many buses, auto rickshaws and taxis. There are several options in buses like such as local buses, deluxe and semi deluxe. Several others like tempos and smaller carrier will take passengers for pre determined fare according to distance.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SHRI RAM MISTHAN BHANDAR, LOCATED AT CHAPRA-PATNA HWY, MOHAN NAGAR, NAI BASTI - (FAMOUS FOR JALEBI AND SHEV BUJIYA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - BHRIGUJI SWEET SHOP, LOCATED AT CHAPRA - REWA - MUZAFFARPUR ROAD, MIRPUR JUARA - (FAMOUS FOR SEW BUNDI MALAI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - AARADHYA BAKER&#39;S POINT, LOCATED AT CHAPRA-PATNA HWY, NAI BASTI - (FAMOUS FOR CAKE, COOKIES, PASTRIES, PIZZA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(590, 14, 31, 734, 'Bihar', 'INDIA', 'DARBHANGA', 'kans-grass-204201_640.jpg', 'kans-grass-204201_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Darbhanga is a wonderful tourist destination and is located in the state of Bihar. The city is one of the significant cities on the map of North Bihar located in the heart of Mithilanchal. &nbsp;Dharbanga is located at a distance of 50 kms from Nepal, making it a place of many tourist pleasures and utility. Dharbhanga is considered as the cultural capital of Bihar. Dharbhanga is a city that excels in the art fields of rich musical form, folk art and traditions from centuries. Darbhanga travel guide brims with the highlights of the architectural marvels and religious places. A wonderful tourist destination, Darbhanga, located in the state of Bihar is a municipal corporation and the capital city of Darbhanga division in the state. It is one of the significant cities of North Bihar, located in the heart of Mithilanchal. The city is considered as the cultural capital of Bihar as the city is rich in its musical form, folk art and traditions from centuries. Darbhanga travel guide is full of references of the architectural marvels and religious places. Darbhanga Fort, Shyama Kali Temple, Mazar of Makhdoom Baba, Holy Rosary Church, Chandradhari Museum and Harahi Pond are the main tourist attractions of the city. The name Darbhanga is the transformation of Dwarbanga i.e. it is the blend of two words, Dwar meaning Gate and Banga meaning Bengal thus signifying Gateway of Bengal. Darbhanga was an antique city of Mithila, which is an ancient cultural region of North India situated between the lower ranges of the Ganga River and the Himalayas.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The city is dotted with numerous hotels ranging from luxury to budget all options of accommodation are available here. Thus, staying in Darbhanga is convenient and enjoyable. Hotels in Darbhanga offer good services and are known for their hospitality which make them a perfect place to stay in.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Dharbhanga Airport is presently under the control of Indian Air Force. And adjoining airports may have to chosen by tourists. The nearest Domestic Airport is Lok Nayak Jayaprakash Airport, Patna, roughly three hour drive from Darbhanga.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Road network is quite good in the city of Darbhanga as several national and state highways pass through this part of Bihar. NH 57 which connects Muzaffarpur to Jhanjhanpur is the major national highway passing through Darbhanga. NH 105 is another national highway crossing through Darbhanga. Major state highways in Darbhanga are SH 50, SH 56 and SH 75 connecting this city within and with surroundings areas and cities as well.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Bus services are quite well and connect this city with other major parts of the country. City bus service and interstate bus service is available for smooth and hassle free transportation in the city of Darbhanga. Bus service is one of the cheapest options of transportation in the city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Darbhanga junction is division of East Central Railways of India. Darbhanga Junction is the important and busiest railway station which comes under Samastipur division. Laheriasarai is another railway station in Darbhanga district which also make transportation easier in this part of Bihar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Auto rickshaws are major part of transport services in Darbhanga as shared autos and rickshaws are also available for local transportation in the city. It is cheapest option that one can choose for moving in the nook and corner of the city. Cycle rickshaws are also available as perfect option for commutation in streets of the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SHANKARANAND SHRBATAALAYA, LOCATED NEAR ROSE PUBLIC SCHOOL - (FAMOUS FOR LASSI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - RAMKUMAR PANDIT HOTEL, NEAR LAHERIASARAI BUS STAND - (FAMOUS FOR KEBAB AND KOFTA)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(591, 14, 31, 734, 'Bihar', 'INDIA', 'MOTIHARI (EAST CHAMPRAN)', 'ficus-320137_640.jpg', 'ficus-320137_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Motihari is the headquarters of East Champaran district located in the Indian state of Bihar. Motihari is a small town in Bihar state famous for many historic events including Mahatma Gandhi&rsquo;s Champaran Satyagrah Quest for truth against the British which started here. The town of Motihari is located in the state of Bihar and is a very popular tourist destination among both pilgrims as well as backpack travellers. The town of Motihari is located at a distance of 156 kilometres from the capital city of Patna. Motihari Tourism is predominantly known for its historical worth. The immense historical worth makes Motihari tourism stand out as a compelling tourist destination. The Mahatma is also credited for helping the town of Motihari reap the fruits of education, as he helped the locals establish a school in the vicinity. The town of Motihari is a magnet for many Buddhist tourists throughout the year, as a major Buddhist stupa is situated here. This stupa is widely known as Motihari stupa and is undeniably a magnificent structure that stands tall at a height of 104 feet. Many believe that the existing stupa is the remains of a much greater stupa. A compelling fact of the Motihari tourism is that the legendary author George Orwell was born here and one can visit George Orwell&rsquo;s monument. The Mahatma Gandhi Museum and Stone Pillar are the most distinguished tourist locations of Motihari Tourism. Motihari embraces many small scale industries such as a paper factory, a sugar mill, and similar industries. Motihari&rsquo;s sugar mill is one of the largest in Bihar. The Motihari agriculture is widely known for its production of litchi fruit and sweet potatoes. The climate of Motihari is quite hot during summers and chilly during winters. One should visit Motihari post monsoon time as it is best suited for the purpose of travel. The climate of Motihari is divided into summer, winter and monsoons, where the summers are hot and humid and the winters get quite chilly.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Quality accommodation is available in Motihari. Staying in luxury hotels will save money with good amenities offered at economical rates. Tourists can enjoy a good stay in the budget hotels that are known to offer best facilities with the best hospitality standards.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Lok Nayak Jayaprakash Airport in Patna is the nearest airport to reach Motihari city. Tourists can also hire local taxis for a cheaper fare to and from the airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Motihari Railway Station is the nearest railway station to reach Motihari. Metered taxis are available on hire for a cheaper price.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Chakia D K S Bus Stand is at a distance of 8.4 kms from Motihari city centre. Govt. owned BSRTC bus services are available on a regular basis to and fro.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Motihari is located near to National Highway 17, which is well connected with other cities within Bihar. Private cabs, non metered auto rickshaws and state transport buses connect various centres of Patna to Motihari.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - MAA ANNAPURNA, LOCATED AT BANK RD, KHUDHA NAGAR, NEAR RAJENDRA NAGAR, RAJENDRA NAGAR - (&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;FAMOUS FOR CAKES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - JAISWAL DHABA, LOCATED AT BHAWANIPUR ZIRAT - (FAMOUS FOR KEBABS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - SHALIMAR SWEETS, LOCATED AT NATIONAL HIGHWAY 28A, RAJENDRA NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR MOTICHOOR KA LADOO, KESARIA PEDA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - N. R. EOODS, LOCATED AT M.S.COLLEGE ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR CHENA MURKI IS A SUGAR COATED &nbsp;SWEET AND GULAB JAMUN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - MOTIHARI - (FAMOUS FOR TASH IS A DISH MADE BY &nbsp;MARINATED MUTTON AND &nbsp;EATEN WITH RICE CALLED CHEWRA)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(592, 14, 31, 734, 'Bihar', 'INDIA', 'GAYA', 'buddha-1915589_1280.jpg', 'buddha-1915589_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">It is a popularly known fact that the founder of Buddhism, Lord Buddha attained enlightenment in Gaya, Bihar and hence the city forms one of the most admired Buddhist destinations. Earlier the city was a part of Magadh and is located 100 kms south of Patna. It is a place sanctified by all the religions. It is surrounded by small rock strewn hills namely Mangala Gauri, Shringa Sthan, Ram Shila and Brahmayoni by three sides and the river flowing on the western side called Phalgu. Gaya city is bounded by Jehnabad district on the north, on the south by Chatra district of Jharkhand. On the east by Nawada district and on the west by Aurangabad district. Gaya tourism offers you beautiful religious destinations that could make anybody spell bound. The place has serenity and peace which is definitely a desired break everyone looks forward to. The Mahabodhi temple is the heart and soul of Gaya tourism. Monks from all over the world turn up to the place and can be spotted sitting at the foot of an enormous carved Buddhist Statute. Gaya tourism is famous for hills like Yoni, Ramshila, Pretishila and caves of Deo Barabar and Pawapuri are also worth mentioning. The ghats and temples are lined on the banks of the sacred river Phalgu. All the destinations are worth visiting for spiritual enrichment. Gaya tourism is embellished by religious and architectural marvels such as Jama Masjid, Manga Gauri Mandir and Vishnupad Temple. The best season to visit Gaya is from October to March. The month of October to March is pleasant and suitable for visiting the attractions in the holy town. The month of June to September is good for short trips and temple visits.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Multiple hotels and guest houses are available here, but prior bookings must be made in peak periods. Monastery guest houses are also a cheaper option than the hotels. There are many religious spots and monasteries in Gaya. To cater to this large influx of tourists, many hotels have come up in Gaya. These are of varying ranges, catering to diverse budgets. Most of the hotels are budget hotels and provide basic facilities at the most affordable prices.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - If one wishes to fly to Gaya, then Gaya is the only city with an international airport in Bihar and Jharkhand taken together. The small airport is connected to Colombo and Bangkok and all major cities in India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Gaya junction is connected to the three metropolises New Delhi, Kolkata and Mumbai through Important Broad Gauge Routes. There are direct trains from Gaya to many important stations in India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - The Grand Trunk Road NH 2, which is undergoing a massive revival under The Golden Quadrilateral project, is about 30 kms from Gaya city. Thus, Gaya is well connected to Kolkata, Varanasi, Allahabad, Kanpur, Delhi as well as Amritsar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Private travel services or state buses are frequently available from all major cities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - GAYA - (FAMOUS FOR MARUA KI ROTI &nbsp;MADE FOM RAAGI FLOUR AND GHEE)<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '');
