(593, 19, 42, 607, 'Catalonia', 'Spain', 'BARCELONA', 'barcelona-680182_640.jpg', 'barcelona-680182_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The city is located on the northeast coast of the Iberian Peninsula, facing the Mediterranean Sea, on a plain approximately 5 km wide. Barcelona is the capital city of Spain, and as well it is the second most populous municipality of the country, with a population of around 1.6 millions within the city limits. Barcelona is one of the leading tourist, economic, trade fair and cultural centre of the world. Its influence in commerce, education, entertainment, media, fashion, science all contribute to its status as one of the world&#39;s major global city. The city also occupies the fame of being a leading smart city in Europe, since 2011. Barcelona is also a transport hub with the Port of Barcelona being one of Europe&#39;s principal seaports and the busiest European passenger port, &nbsp;with an international airport, Barcelona&ndash;El Prat Airport, it has an extensive motorway network and a high-speed rail line with a link to France and the rest of Europe. The city is the home of many points of interest declared as World Heritage Sites by UNESCO.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Barcelona offers a wide range of accommodations options ranging from budget and medium hotels to luxury hotels. The city also offers wide range of apartments,and rooms on rental basis one can enjoy the facility of such places from budget to luxury all across the city.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - the city is served by Barcelona-El Prat Airport lies &nbsp;about 17 km from the centre of Barcelona. It is the largest airport on the Mediterranean coast, and the second-largest airport in the Spain. The airport is the main hub for Vueling Airlines and Ryanair also focuses for Iberia and Air Europa. The airport mainly serves domestic and European destinations. &nbsp;The airport is well connected to the city by highway, metro, commuter train and scheduled bus service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Barcelona lies on three international routes, including European route E15 that follows the Mediterranean coast, E90 to Madrid and Lisbon, and E09 to Paris. The city is also served with a comprehensive network of motorways and highways throughout the metropolitan areas. The city&#39;s main arteries include Diagonal Avenue, which crosses it diagonally, Meridiana Avenue which leads to Gl&ograve;ries and connects with Diagonal Avenue and Gran Via de les Corts Catalanes, which crosses the city from east to west, passing through its centre.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Barcelona is a major hub for RENFE, the Spanish state railway network. The city&#39;s main Inter-city rail station is Barcelona Sants railway station and Estacio de Fran&ccedil;a terminus serves a secondary role handling suburban, regional and medium distance services.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Barcelona is served by a comprehensive local public transport network that includes a metro, a bus network, two separate modern tram networks, a separate historic tram line, and several funiculars and aerial cable cars. Barcelona has a metered taxi fleet governed by the Institut Metropolit&agrave; del Taxi. On 22 March 2007 Barcelona&#39;s City Council started the Bicing service, a bicycle service understood as a public transport. The user can own their user card and they can take a bicycle from any of the more than 400 stations spread around the city and use it anywhere in the city, and can leave the bicycle at any station.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>BARCELONA - [FAMOUS FOR FIDEUA MADE WITH NOODLES INSTEAD OF RICE ; ALLIOLI IS A SAUCE MADE WITH GARLIC OLIVE OIL AND SALT ; ESCALIVADA IS A SALAD MADE OF EGGPLANT, PEPPERS, TOMATOES ONIONS AND VINEGER ; CREMA CATALANA IS A CUSTOARD DESERT ; MEL I MATO IS AFRESH UNSALTED SOFT CHEESE ; SUQUET DE PEIX (POTATO BASED SEAFOOD STEW) ; ESQUEIXADA IS A SALAD CONSISTS OF BACALAO OR SALT COD WITH PEPPERS, TOMATOES, ONIONS AND OLIVES ; &nbsp;ESPINACS AMB PANSES I PINYONS SAUTEED SPINACH WITH RAISINS AND PINE NUTS ; AMANIDA CATAALANA IS MIXED SALAD AND COLD MEATS ; MACARRONS(MACRONI WITH BOLOGNESE SAUCE ; CARN ARREBOSSADA(CRUMBED MEAT(CHICKEN OR BEEF)] &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(594, 16, 43, 1551, 'New York', 'U.S.A', 'NEW YORK', 'new-york-540807_6401.jpg', 'new-york-540807_6402.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The largest and most populous city in the United States, New York is situated on the mouth of the Hudson River. Spanning a land area of 305 square miles, the city lies in the southernmost part of the state, which is part of the Mid Atlantic region of the United States. Manhattan is a famous island between the Hudson and East Rivers. The most populous borough, Brooklyn is located south and east of Manhattan across the East River. Located to the east of Manhattan, across the East River, Queens is a U-shaped neighbourhood. The county is the most ethnically diverse region in the United States and one of the most diverse in the world. Bronx is situated north of Manhattan Island. One of the most cosmopolitan cities in the world, the destination has immigrants from over 180 countries. The major tourist seasons in the city are fall and spring. From September to November and from April to June, the city is a heaven for tourists.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">New York City offers a wide range of accommodations to fit every taste: marquee hotels that reflect NYC&rsquo;s bright lights, boutique hotels tucked away on charming side streets, family friendly stays close to parks and greenery. Whether looking to visit nearby attractions explore NYC history or be in the centre of it all, these hotels will make New York City your home away from home.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - If coming from far away, tourists will probably want to fly into one of the New York City area&rsquo;s major airports. There are a number of hotels conveniently located near the City&rsquo;s airports.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Those starting from a nearby suburb can reach NYC by NJ Transit, Long Island Rail Road or Metro North Railroad. Amtrak also offers comfortable, convenient service to NYC from cities near and far.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- For some travellers, especially those coming from other East Coast cities, buses are an affordable and convenient travel option. New York City enjoys service from such companies as Megabus, Bolt Bus and Greyhound, as well as other local carriers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - New York is an excellent walking city, and getting around by foot is the best way to familiarize with neighbourhoods and their divisions. Sometimes to cover great distances, buses and cabs are available. A Metro Card gives access to trains and buses that travel to every corner of the city.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Other Modes</strong> - &nbsp;Ferries, pedi-cabs, cruise ships, bicycles and even helicopters are all great ways to get around New York.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - BLUE RIBBON BRASSERIE, AT 97 SUVLLIAN STREET NEW YORK - [FAMOUS FOR BONE MARROW (WITH A MIXTURE OF SALTY BRAISED OXTAIL, VEGETABLES AND HERBS)]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - VESELKA, AT 144 2AVENUE - [FAMOUS FOR PIEROGI(STUFFED DUMPLINGS( WITH SOUR CREAM FRIED ONIONS AND APPLE SAUCE]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - ROEBLING TEA ROOM, AT 143 ROEBLING STREET - [FAMOUS FOR CHEDDAR EGGS WITH RAISIN FENNEL TOAST AND APPLE BUTTER]<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - SHAKE SHACK&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;MADISON, AT SQUARE PARK - [FAMOUS FOR ANGUS BEEF BURGER OR VEGGIE MUSHROOM-FILLED SHROOM BURGER]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - KATZ DELICATESSEN, AT 205 EAST HOUSTON STREET - [FAMOUS FOR PASTRAMI SANDWICH]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - EILEEN&#39;S, AT 17 CLEVELAND PLACE - [FAMOUS FOR CHEESECAKE]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - NATHAN&#39;S FAMOUS, AT 1310 SURF AVENUE - [FAMOUS FOR HOTDOGS]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>8 - BRENNAN AND CARR, AT 3432 NOSTRAND AVE, BROOKLYN - [FAMOUS FOR BEEF SANDWICH]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>9- JOE&#39;S PIZZA, AT 7 CARMINE STREET - [FAMOUS FOR A PLAIN SLICE]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>10 - MOMOFUKU NOODLE BAR, AT 171 1ST AVENUE - [FAMOUS FOR PORK BUNS]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>11 - GRAND CENTRAL OYSTER BAR, AT 89 E 42ND STREET - [FAMOUS FOR THE OYSTER PAN ROAST]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>12 - KEENS STEAKHOUSE, AT 72 W 36TH STREET - [FAMOUS FOR MUTTON CHOP]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>13 - 21 CLUB, AT 21 W 52ND STREET - [FAMOUS FOR THE CHICKEN HASH]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>14 - GLASER&#39;S BAKE SHOP, AT 1670 1ST AVENUE - [FAMOUS FOR BLACK AND WHITE COOKIE]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>15 - RUSS AND DAUGHTERS, AT 179 E HOUSTON STREET - [FAMOUS FOR BAGEL AND LOX]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(595, 18, 44, 0, '', 'Antarctica', 'ANTARCTICA', 'iceberg-404966_640.jpg', 'iceberg-404966_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Antarctica, the southernmost continent and site of the South Pole, is a virtually uninhabited, ice covered landmass. Most cruises to the continent visit the Antarctic Peninsula, which stretches toward South America. It&rsquo;s known for the Lemaire Channel and Paradise Harbour, striking, iceberg flanked passageways, and Port Lockroy, a former British research station turned museum. The peninsula&rsquo;s isolated terrain also shelters rich wildlife, including many penguins. The people who travel to or live in Antarctica fall into two main groups, those who live and work on scientific research stations or bases, and tourists. No one lives in Antarctica indefinitely in the way that they do in the rest of the world. It has no commercial industries, no towns or cities, no permanent residents.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are no hotels in the pristine lands of Antarctica that continue to remain unaffected by human activities in the region. Accommodation is restricted to the expedition vessels which transfer people to different parts of the continent.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Blanketed in snow, the continent of Antarctica was barely accessible via commercial services a few years ago. However, an increasing interest in the region led to the development of a flight service known as Air Cruise, which takes off from Punta Arenas in Chile. Air Cruise takes three hours to reach the aerodrome of King George Island, where cruise ships make arrangements for the upcoming journey through the continent. Besides this, the airport atHobart in Australia caters to flights heading towards the Wilkins Aerodrome that serves as a gateway to the ice capped region. This facility is only open for scientists and researchers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Sea</strong> - A diverse range of vessels navigate through the Antarctic, paving their way amidst gigantic glaciers. There&rsquo;s a choice between a vast array of sailboats and smaller vessels. The latter are preferred over larger vessels as they&rsquo;re permitted to dock at any place, enabling travellers to explore the serene shores. Commonly, a cruise spans over two or more weeks and schedules depend strictly on prevailing conditions of weather. Cruise ships leave from theUshuaia Port at Argentina for a round trip to the virgin fields of the Antarctic. In the east, the port of Hobart in Tasmania, Australia receives charter yachts that sail towards the coastal strip of the continental landmass of Antarctica.Christchurch in New Zealand and Port Elizabeth in South Africa provide similar services.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>ANTARCTICA - {FAMOUS FOR HOOSH &nbsp;IS A STEW MADE FROM PEMMICAN (A MIXTURE OF DRIED MEAT, FAT, AND CEREAL) ; SLEDGING BISCUIT MADE FROM FLOUR, BAKING SODA AND BUTTER ; ERNEST SHACkLETON&#39;S BANNOCKS &nbsp;IS A TYPE OF FLATBREAD MADE FROM PLAIN WHITE FLOUR, BAKING POWDER AND BUTTER}&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(596, 22, 45, 0, 'New South Wales', 'Australia', 'SYDNEY', 'sydney-363244_1280.jpg', 'sydney-363244_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">One of Australia&rsquo;s most happening and culturally diverse cities, Sydney is a conglomeration of exquisite beaches, architectural marvels, fantastic restaurants, fabulous scenery, adventurous activities and most importantly, friendly locals. What&rsquo;s more, Sydney is home to people from diverse backgrounds and is the melting pot of many cultures. It is not without reason that it is one of the most ethnically and culturally diverse cities not just in Australia but across the world. One of the loveliest harbour cities, Sydney is a city of global repute and not only in the tourism sector. The vast sightseeing options, numerous activities and the cultural cauldron of Sydney have made it one of the most sought after holiday destinations. The beautiful beaches of Sydney would perhaps be the first one to catch your attention. And boy, are they beautiful! On the beaches, it&rsquo;s your call to either go wild and race across the sands or go challenge the waves on a surfboard, or you might just take a chill pill and relax at the sunny warm beaches. Visit stunning masterpieces of architecture like the Sydney Opera House, Darling Harbour, Taronga Zoo, Centennial Park and Hyde Park Barracks Museum. Jump aboard a ferry and go cruising in the evening, from the ferries, the city looks like a fairyland with twinkling and sparkling lights. Enjoy the happening nightlife of Sydney at the most famous bars and pubs nurturing a glass of wine and humming away to the music in the background. Enthralling theatre and stage performances would keep you entertained on any evening you choose to visit the numerous theatres in Sydney.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Sydney offers both a huge quantity and variety of accommodation, with solid options in every price range. Even so, the supply shrivels up under the summer sun, particularly around weekends and big events. Predictably, views play a big part in determining room prices here the wallet will shed kilos as one rides the hotel elevator up to lofty harbour view suite.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Sydney Kingsford Smith International Airport is the busiest international airport of Australia. It is well connected with the major cities of the world. The airport is also very well linked with the other international as well as domestic airports in Australia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Sydney is well connected by rail to Canberra, Melbourne, Brisbane and Adelaide. There are railway links between New South Wales and Perth, Alice Springs and Adelaide as well. Many trains and buses from the Central Station in Sydney are operated by government&rsquo;s country link.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Sydney is one of the major Australian cities and is very well connected by road to other cities. The roads are good and cars are easily available on rent. Driving in Australia is on the left and it is mandatory for all foreign visitors to have an International Driver&rsquo;s License.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Private as well as government run buses link Sydney, New South Wales to other parts of the country and most of these buses arrive at Sydney Coach Terminal. All buses and coaches are equipped with safety and comfort features to make your travel as convenient as possible. However, government bus services are more economical than the private ones. Travelling by road also gives you a chance to enjoy the beautiful scenery along the Pacific Highway.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - SYDNEY - [FAMOUS FOR LAMINGTONS IS A NATIONAL CAKE OF AUSTRALIA ; CHIKO ROLL(IS A SNACK CONTAINS BEEF, CELERY, CABBAGE, BARLEY,CARROT,ONION, GREEN BEANS AND SPICES) ; ANZAC BISCUITS(ROLLED OATS, FLOUR, SUGAR,COCONUT,GOLDEN SYRUP WITH BUTTER) ; ICED VOVO(IS AWHEAT FLOUR BISCUIT TOPPED WITH RASPBERRY JAM) ; PAVLOVA(IS A MERINGUE BASED DESERT) ; PRAWN COCKTAIL ALSO CALLED SHRIMP COCKTAIL(IS A SEAFOOD DISH CONSISTING OF SHELLED, PRAWNS IN A COCKTAIL SAUCE) ; CORN DOG(IS A SAUSAGE COATED IN THICK LAYER OF CORNMEAL BATTER ON A STICK)]&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - SWEET BELEM, AT 35B NEW CANTERBURY ROAD, PETERSHAM - [FAMOUS FOR TRAT (PUFF PASTRY)]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - QUAY, AT OVERSEAS PASSENGER TERMINAL, HICKSON ROAD - [FAMOUS FOR SNOW EGG]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - MARRICKVILLE PORK ROLL, AT 236A ILLAWARRA ROAD, MARRICKVILLE - [FAMOUS FOR PORK BANH MI (PORK ROLL)]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n5 - ROCKPOOL, AT 11 BRIGE STREET SYDNEY - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;DATE TRAT]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n6 - TAN VIET, AT 2/100 JOHN STREET, CABRAMATTA - [FAMOUS FOR CRISKIN CHICKEN]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n7 - LUCIO&#39;S, AT&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;47 WINDSOR STREET, PADDINGTON - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;GREEN NOODLES WITH BLUE SWIMMER CRAB]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n8 - BUON RICORDO, AT 108 BOUNDARY STREET,PADDINGTON - [FAMOUS FOR TRUFFLED EGG PASTA]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n9 - PASTICCERIA PAPA, AT 145 RAMSAY STREET, HABERFIELD AND 75 HALL STREET, BONDI BEACH - [FAMOUS FOR RICOTTA CAKE]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(597, 14, 31, 734, 'Bihar', 'INDIA', 'GOPALGANJ', 'india-978490_640.jpg', 'india-978490_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Gopalganj is a town, municipality and headquarters of Gopalganj district in the Indian state of Bihar. It was carved out of old Saran district on October 2, 1973. Gopalganj was part of erstwhile Saran district which encompassed Chhapra, Siwan and Gopalganj. In the 18th century, it was ruled by Hathwa Raj, which encompassed 1365 villages. Gopalganj covers 2033 sq kms of area and ranks as the 26th largest district in the state of Bihar. In the western part, it has Gandak River flowing southwards. It is mostly plains and fertile land. It is located at an average elevation of 66 mts above sea level. It is situated in the Northwest of Bihar State and is a border district, touching Indian state of Uttar Pradesh. Gopalganj is adjoined to the West Champaran district in the north, the place where Mahatma Gandhi started his revolution for independence, the Satyagrah Andolan, East Champaran district in east, Chhapra district in southeast, Siwan district in South, Deoria district in West and Kushinagar district in northwest. The district is adjacent to the famous Valmiki National Park. One of the great Hindu shrines, the goddess of thawe, is located in this district. The magnificent fort erected by King of Hathwa, though in decadent state today but is a place of historical value. Near the fort are fourteen small mounds marking the spot where 14 ladies sacrificed their life owing to Sati Pratha. Nearby palace is an ancient Durga temple. In the premises of the temple a peculiar tree has grown up in cross shape. It has been a matter of research even today as its botanical family has not yet been identified.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are several private lodges and government owned inspection bungalows where rooms are available at affordable rates.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - Sabeyan Hawai Adda is the closest airport in Gopalganj.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - The junction is the closest one Siwan or Thawe Railway junction about 2 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Raod</strong> - It has good road network in the state that links different places within the state along with other parts of the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Bus</strong> - Regular Private and state bus services are available from major cities of Bihar and also from neighbouring states.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SHANKAR, LOCATED AT CHHAPRA - GOPALGANJ ROAD, PAL NAGAR, ATARSUA - (FAMOUS FOR GULAB JAMUN AND BESAN LADOO)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - K CHAUDHARY SWEETS, LOCATED AT CINEMA ROAD, WARD NO. 15 - (FAMOUS FOR BURGERS)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(598, 14, 31, 734, 'Bihar', 'INDIA', 'HAJIPUR', 'cherry-tomato-1707523_1280.jpg', 'cherry-tomato-1707523_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\nHajipur town is the main headquarters of Vaishali district of Bihar and is known for its bountiful banana production. The town is famed as one of the most progressive towns of Bihar. Hajipur tourism has become one of the hot destinations on a traveller&rsquo;s map. There is a modern Railway Zone Office in the town. What adds to the real charm of Hajipur tourism is the exquisiteness of the Ganges River surrounding it in the south and Narayani and Gandak Rivers in the west. The place is well known for mouth watering fruits like litchis and bananas. Haji Ilyas Shah who was the king of Bengal founded Hajipur. It is believed that in ancient times the city was named Ukkacala. What draws tourists from all over the world is the treasure of magnificent temples that the Hajipur tourism takes immense pride in. The place is surrounded by rivers which blesses Hajipur with a moderate sort of weather. October to March is the ideal time to visit the place. People who are planning for vacations can spend wonderful time in the city, soaking in many delights of Hajipur tourism. The onset of winters, especially October can be targeted because of the friendly weather conditions. Rest of the year has extreme heat and heavy monsoons which may pose an obstruction to enjoyment.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The hotels in the city like Hajipur offer a wide range of cuisine and lodging facilities to the tourists visiting the city. Apart from hospitality services the hotels have tie up with several travel agents which help in assisting the tourists. Most of the hotels in Hajipur are well equipped to serve the basic requirements of its customers.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Patna Airport serves the city of Hajipur and is around 23 kms away. Patna airport is well connected through road.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Railway connects Hajipur to Muzaffarpur, Chhapra, and Barauni. Important trains like Guwahati Rajdhani express, Vaishali Express and many other notable trains halt in Hajipur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Hajipur is connected to other parts of India through national and state highways. Major highway is National Highway 19 which touches the city and connects it to Chhapra that further joins Ghazipur city in Uttar Pradesh.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - HAJIPUR - (FAMOUS FOR KHAJA IS A DESERT DEEP ERIED ELAKY PIE DIPPED IN SUGAR SYRUP)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - RAGHUKUL STALL, LOCATED AT VAISHALI - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - PUSHPANJALI SWEET SHOP, LOCATED AT NEAR CENTERAL BANK OE INDIA, MAHNAR ROAD,HAJIPUR - (FAMOUS FOR PARWAL KI MITHAI AND KALA JAMUN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - HARILAL&#39;S THE SWEET SHOPPE,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT WEST BORING CANAL ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORI, JALEBI AND PAW BHAJI)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(599, 14, 31, 733, 'Assam', 'INDIA', 'JEHANABAD', 'paddy-harvest-207960_640.jpg', 'paddy-harvest-207960_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Jehanabad is an agricultural city and a municipality in and the headquarters of Jehanabad district existing in the Indian state of Bihar. Previously, Jehanabad was part of Gaya district. Several rivers such as Falgu, Dardha, Jamuna and Morhar flow after crossing the district&#39;s plan topography. Presently, Jehanabad is divided into two parts, one is Jehanabad and the other being Arwal. Jehanabad had derived its name from Jahanabad, which was named after the great Mughal emperor Shah Jahan. Jehanabad was created as a separate district with the strong desire to increase the extent of developmental activities that take place in the region. As far as minerals are considered, the entire region of Jehanabad has only minor ones. The forest range of the district is restricted to 10.3 sq kms, which is chiefly concentrated near the Barabar Hills. They represent the reserve forest area. Jehanabad history runs pretty much parallel with Bihar history. There is nothing to distinguish between the two. Both have witnessed the rise and fall of many important empires. The most important was Maghdha Empire an empire that made entire Bihar region its citadel during ancient period. Nonetheless, any discussion about Jehanabad history would be incomplete without mentioning how Jehanabad city got its name. Jehanabad was actually named after Jahanara Begum Sahib, daughter of the famous Mughal Emperor Shah Jahan.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Unfortunately, tourist infrastructure in Jehanabad is still underdeveloped. Hence here there are no luxurious hotels. All that tourists will get here is few ordinary lodges and hotels.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Lok Nayak Jayaprakash Airport in Patna is the nearest airport to reach Jehanabad. The distance covered is 42.96 kms.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Jehanabad has a railway station of its own within the city. There are four railway stations for accessing the city such as Jehanabad, Court, Tehta and Makhdumpur in the 31 kms long stretch of the railways.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Jehanabad Bus Stand can be easily accessed by tourists because regular bus services from BSRTC are available for traveller&rsquo;s convenience. There are also many private bus companies on or near Station Road.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Jehanabad has got one of the best road networks in Bihar. National Highway 83 originates from Patna via Masaurhi, extends directly to Gaya through Makhdumpur and runs almost parallel along with the railway line.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - RASOI RESTAURANT AND EAST EOOD, LOCATED AT OPP SHIVA JEE PATH - (FAMOUS FOR DAL ERY, MATAR PANEER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - ZAIKA, LOCATED AT JEHANABAD - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN BIRYANI, CHICKEN TANDOORI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - MURARI JI, LOCATED AT GANDHI MAIDAAN - (FAMOUS FOR PANIPURI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - JEHANABAD - {FAMOUS FOR THEKUA IS A SWEET MADE EROM WHEAT ELOUR, CHASNI (MELTED SUGAR) AND GHEE ; TRADITIONAL SWEET DISHES LIKE RABRI/BASUNDI, KHEER, GULAB JAMUN, MALPUA, CHURMA DURING CHHATH PUJA}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(600, 14, 31, 734, 'Bihar', 'INDIA', 'JAMUI', 'crimson-rose-301449_1280.jpg', 'crimson-rose-301449_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Jamui, one of the famous districts of Bihar, is mainly known for its mythological and historical importance for Jain religion. Presently counted among 38 Bihar districts, Jamui has been in limelight from the time of Mahabharata. Another reason for which Jaimui tourism is considered a worthwhile destination is due to a legend which proclaims that the name Jamui has been derived from Jribhikgram or Jambhiyaagram the village that is known for being the spot where Lord Mahavir attained Divine Knowledge or Kevalaygyan. Jaimui has been a fertile ground for the development of rich literature and music in the region, some of the celebrated gems from the arts domain, hail from Jaimui. Jaimui tourism harbours several spots of great historical interest and mythological importance. The best time to plan a trip to Jaimui is from July to November before the onset of the harsh winters.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Jamui offers good accommodation facilities for a nominal price. Tourists get to find premium amenities best fitting their budgets. Most of the hotels allocate dedicated rooms to those who book early. Luxury resorts also help tourists in having a gala time in the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air</strong> - The Patna International Airport is just 161 kms away while the Gaya International Airport is just 141 kms away from here.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Train</strong> - Jamui is one of the main railway junctions of Danapur division of East Central Railway. It lies on the Howrah Patna Mughalsarai main line.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Road </strong>- One can reach Jaimui from any metropolitan city located along the Delhi Kolkata Main Road that connects Mugalsarai Patna route. This route runs parallel to the famous Grand Trunk Road.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(601, 14, 31, 734, 'Bihar', 'INDIA', 'KAIMUR', 'kans-grass-204147_6402.jpg', 'kans-grass-204147_6403.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kaimur has a glorious heritage and is one the most vibrant regions of Bihar. Kaimur is an administrative district lying in the western portion of Bihar with main headquarters of the district being located at Bhabua. The plains are lush and productive alluvial lands while the plateau regions are rocky. The rivers Karmanasha, Durgawati and Kudra border the city. From the 6th BC and 5th AD Kaimur was an integral part of the Magadh Empire ruled by the pre-Mauryans and also the late Gupta rulers of Magadh. Kaimur has made an enormous contribution in the Indian Freedom movement. Kaimur tourism offers a taste of everything and doesn&rsquo;t disappoint its tourists. Telhar is a beautiful waterfall located near B.T. Road in Kaimur. Set in a natural setting the waterfalls is a great feast for the eyes. Kaimur is a host to a large number of Hindu festivals and melas, each celebrated at different pilgrim hubs and temples. Hordes of tourists as well as pilgrims visit Kaimur to observe it&rsquo;s tranquil from close quarters. The Kaimur region experiences varied climatic conditions which vary according to different seasons. While summers are hot winters can also be on the extreme, making the period from October to March the best time to travel to the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are not many good hotels and lodges to stay in Kaimur. The only good hotel here is Hotel Kaimur. Hotel Kaimur is an initiative of Bihar State Tourism Development Corporation and hence the hotel is very cost effective and provides all basic facilities to its visitors. There are also few guesthouses available in Kaimur.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\n<strong>By Air</strong> - There is no independent airport in Kaimur and anyone who wishes to access the city by air will have to connect through Varanasi Airport, which is the nearest airport. Varanasi is 60 kms from Kaimur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Mohania is the only major railway junction of district. Commonly the station is known as Bhabua Road on the Howrah New Delhi Grand Card located in the Mughalsarai region. A large number of trains connect the city to almost all states and important cities of the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong>- Kaimur is 200 kms from Patna and 100 kms from Varanasi. National Highway 30 connects Kaimur with the capital Patna via Arrah. Apart from this, there are also a few State Highways in the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - VRINDAVAN SWEETS &amp; RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT MAHAMAYA COMPLEX,SHEOSAGAR,BIHAR, SH 67, DELHI - KOLKATA HWY - (FAMOUS FOR RASMALAI AND SOUTH INDIAN EOOD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - GREEN PLANNET EXPRESS RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT NEAR MICO, GT ROAD, DILIA - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA, BURGERS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - WAH LAJAWAB RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT OLD G T ROAD SASARAM, IN ERONT OE NEHRU PARK, SASARAM - (FAMOUS FOR PANEER CHILLI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - TIWARI &nbsp;BHANDAR, LOCATED AT BHABUA - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;TILKUT)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(602, 14, 31, 734, 'Bihar', 'INDIA', 'MADHUBANI', 'woman-978343_640.jpg', 'woman-978343_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><br />\r\nMadhubani district is a part of Darbhanga Division. The origins of Madhubani could be traced back to the Darbhanga district and it became a district in 1972. Many literary figures were born here. In fact the perception is that Madhubani was the second city to adopt democracy. The word Madhubani is derived from the Hindi word in which Madhu means sweet and bani means voice. The people here are supposed to have that pleasant and sweet voice. The main language spoken here is Mithilla whereas Hindi, English and Urdu is also read and understood by people here. The place is situated about 56 mts above the sea level and has great archaeological and religious treasures in the form of temples and shrines. Tourists visit the place throughout the year. One can see the traces of early medieval period in the archaeology of Madhubani. Spinning and weaving are also important aspects of Mithillan Handicrafts and are popular all over the nation. Though it&rsquo;s usually the women who participate in making of these handicrafts but the handicrafts of the region are a great example of the rich quality of handloom textile of the region. Madhubani tourism is blessed with a vast variety of archaeological treasures. The Madubani style of paintings are also made here using vegetable dyes, lamp black and the canvas here is sometimes even made of paper, though the canvas of cloth is also used at times. Madhubani Lokgeet is also very popular amongst the region. The Madhubani tourism is enchanting and every traveller who has witnessed the charm of Madhubani can&rsquo;t deny the beauty and heritage of the place. Madhubani tourism offers a spectacular tourist destination and should be visited at least once. The temple dedicated to Bhagwati and the temple of Ugarnath remains on the top of &lsquo;to visit&rsquo; list of the tourists. And till date they remain one of the most famous tourist magnets of the Madhubani tourism.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">A number of budget, mid size and luxury hotels are present in the city of Madhubani which offer comfortable stay at reasonable prices. One may also pre book hotels online to avoid last minute hassles as well as avail some discounts. The hotels in Madhubani offer all basic facilities like room service, hot water, ACs, meals, etc. with good quality.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air</strong> - Patna airport is 128 kms away from Madhubani and has constant flights from most metro cities of the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Road</strong> - Well connected to nearby cities via road. State tourism and private buses run regularly across the borders of the city. Cars and taxies are also available.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Train</strong> - Madhubani has a small station of its own, not majorly linked via direct trains. Trains can be taken to Madhubani by changing in Patna or Darbhanga junction. There are selected direct trains available from major metros.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - State buses and private buses are available to travel to and within the city. Other than that, people travel within the city by sharing taxies, jeeps and autos. When going to nearby places, one can also commute by cycle rickshaws.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(603, 14, 31, 734, 'Bihar', 'INDIA', 'MUNGER', 'door-shield-1182849_640.jpg', 'door-shield-1182849_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Munger city is located in Bihar and is perhaps one of the most alluring cities of Bihar. Munger tourism is one of the best choices a tourist can have. It is a real treat in terms of the tourist attractions it has to offer. The city made its presence felt all through historical times and served as the capital of Bengal under the rule of Kasim Ali Khan in 1762. The city of Munger has many distinctions to its name. It is interesting to note that during the First World War, it was the city of Munger that produced cartridge guns. Even during the Indo China war the Munger gun factory played a crucial role in 1962. Munger city is rich in scenic beauty by virtue of its location on the bank of River Ganga. The presence of divine ghats in the city&rsquo;s proximity adds the mesmerising view. Munger is blessed with immense wealth of historical and religious sites that are simply a treat to experience. Munger tourism is the hub of many enthusiastic tourists because of major highlights such as the grandeur of architecture of the Munger Fort which is built on a mound and has been there since medieval era. Munger is known for the work expertise in iron, articles cast in iron are a special craft. The festivities that embellish Munger tourism are Chatt Puja, Durga Puja, Raksha Bandhan, and Christmas. Munger gets really hot and dry in summers and bitterly cold in winters. Monsoons are fair here and so the best time to plan a trip is from September to March.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Munger being a popular tourist destination is home to numerous hotels and lodges. From luxury to mid range, economical and budget hotel every option are available to meet the various needs of the visitors. Staying in these hotels can be a memorable experience as tourist will be wonder to find that despite located in a small town they offer whole range of facilities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Lok Nayak Jayaprakash Airport, Patna is the closest airport which linked it to all major Indian cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Jamalpur is the closest junction to Munger, which linked it to all major cities and states .It has its own junction also.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- It is connected with National Highway 80 and various other state highways.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - State buses and private buses are easily available from or to Munger to all major towns of the state and also with neighbouring state.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - MUNGER - [FAMOUS FOR GHUNGI IS A SNACK(BLACK GRAM OR DRIED YELLOW PEAS OR DRIED WHITE PEAS ARE USED WITH GRAVY) ; PITHA IS ASNACK MADE FROM RICE FLOUR OR WHEAT FLOUR]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(604, 14, 31, 734, 'Bihar', 'INDIA', 'MUZAFFARPUR', 'tomatoes-1697202_640.jpg', 'tomatoes-1697202_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Muzaffarpur is the largest city situated in the northern part of Bihar and is located around 35 kms from Vaishali on the banks of River Burhi Gandak. Purbi Champaran and Sitamarhi districts in the northern regions and Vaishali and Saran districts in the southern part bound Muzaffarpur. Known as the Lychee Capital of India, Muzaffarpur is one of the most popular centres for trade in India. The major transactions of trade for Muzaffarpur are with Nepal, in which grains and other commodities are exchanged. Owing to its world renowned Shahi Lychee and Chinese Lychee fruits, it has won several international accolades. Muzaffarpur was named after Muzaffar Khan, who was a revenue officer in the early 18th century. Earlier the areas of Champaran, Darbhanga and Muzaffarpur were combined and altogether were known by the name of Vaishali. This region used to be the centre of power and authority of the Linchavi Kingdom. Ancient sites and Buddhist Viharas are an integral part of Muzaffarpur cultural heritage. Some of the popular destinations here include ancient temples like the Kali Temple of Sikandarpur, the Rajeshwari Devi Mandir, Chaturbhuj Temple, Ramna&#39;s Tripur Sundari Temple, Shri Ram Temple, and Baba Garib Stan, the shrine dedicated to Lord Shiva. There are also several shrines, temples and Buddhist monasteries in the regions of Vaishali and Rajgir. Besides, the nearby locations Rajgir and Vaishali are famous for the historic places of Buddhist significance. Nalanda attracts numerous tourists for its remnants of stupas, monasteries, temples and the Nalanda University, and the excavated artefacts are displayed in the Nalanda Museum.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Owing to its commercial importance, Muzaffarpur surely doesn&rsquo;t have any dearth of hotels. Today there are enough hotels to choose from right from luxury hotels to budget hotels. Most of the hotels in Muzaffarpur are equipped with basic amenities and ensure utmost comfort and satisfaction of their customers.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Muzaffarpur does a have airport, but it is a non operational airport. The nearest operational airport is Jaiprakash Narayan International Airport popularly known as Patna airport in capital city Patna. It is located barely 80 kms away from main city of Muzaffarpur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Muzaffarpur Railway Station is main railway station of Muzaffarpur District and is one of the busiest junctions of Bihar. It directly connects Muzaffarpur to almost all the important cities of India including of course all the important cities of Bihar too.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Road notwork in Muzaffarpur is quite impressive. Various national and state highways connect it to many other parts of the country. National Highway 57, NH 28, NH 77 and NH 102 pass through Muzaffarpur district. NH 57 passes only through Bihar state and connects Muzaffarpur to Purnea district. NH 28 directly connects Muzaffarpur to many of the important cities of Bihar and Uttar Pradesh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Auto rickshaw is the most popular local transportation, though its usage is mainly restricted to main city of Muzaffarpur and other city areas of the district. Here auto rickshaws run on the concept of shared auto rickshaws. Besides auto rickshaw, govt owned city ring buses that only ply in main city of Muzaffarpur is another popular and reliable local transportation.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - VAISHALI SWEETS, NEAR CHATTA CHOWK - (FAMOUS FOR RASGULLA, RASMADHURI AND CHAT)<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(605, 14, 31, 734, 'Bihar', 'INDIA', 'NALANDA', 'dhanushkodi-1765163_6402.jpg', 'dhanushkodi-1765163_6403.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Speak of Nalanda and the mind conjures up images of monks in maroon coloured robes, of chants and hymns, of scripts and knowledge, which was cosmic in nature and the meditating Buddha. Founded in the 5th century AD, the city is said to have got its name from the Sanskrit word Nalanda, which if broken in two, means giver of knowledge. True to its name, the University of Nalanda was undisputedly the epicentre of learning in ancient India. The rich past of Nalanda can be ascertained by the fact that scholars from Tibet, China, Turkey, Greece and Persia etc. and students from far and wide came here to seek knowledge. It enjoys the stature of one of the first residential universities in the world. It was home to 2000 teachers and 10000 students from all over the world, who studied here. Nalanda shone on the world map after the Chinese traveller Hieun Tsang came here in the 7th century. He not only wrote elaborately about its unique and exceptional education system followed by thousands of monk, but he also took with him texts, which were later translated in Chinese. Situated around 90 kms from Patna, the capital city of Bihar, Nalanda was considered an architectural marvel, which has been neatly preserved by Nalanda tourism. Built with red bricks, the complex was spread over an area of 14 hectares. It had temples, classrooms, meditation halls, lakes and parks. The library was located in a nine storied building where scriptures and ancient texts were painstakingly written and preserved.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Tourists visiting Nalanda often prefer to stay in Rajgir, known for its wide range of accommodation options including luxury hotels. But for tourists who wish to stay in Nalanda itself, the city provides modest accommodation options within the budget. The hotels in Nalanda are known for their hospitality, and providing basic amenities and clean ambiance.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Lok Nayak Jayaprakash International Airport at Patna is the nearest airport to Nalanda which is located at a distance of 90 kms. Flights from all major cities of India are connected to Patna.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Rajgir is the nearest railway station to reach Nalanda. However, the nearest and major convenient rail head is at Gaya.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - BSRTC operates buses at regular intervals to all parts of Nalanda, which is connected well through buses to other cities as well such as Rajgir, Gaya, Patna, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Nalanda being located on NH 82, it is well connected by good network of roads to Patna, Bodhgaya, Gaya and other important cities of Bihar State.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><br />\r\n1 - NALANDA - (FAMOUS FOR DHUSKA IS A SNACK MADE FROM CHANNA DAL AND RICE)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '');
INSERT INTO `city` (`id`, `continent_id`, `country_id`, `state_id`, `state_name`, `country_name`, `ci_name`, `main_image`, `main_image1`, `description`, `accomdation`, `transportation`, `eatable`, `experience_type_id`) VALUES
(606, 14, 31, 734, 'Bihar', 'INDIA', 'NAWADA', 'wild-allamanda-348888_12802.jpg', 'wild-allamanda-348888_12803.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Nawada is located in the southern Bihar. Earlier it was a part of Gaya district. Nawada in historical times was ruled by dynasties like Brihadratha, Maurya, Kanah and the Gupta. In the era of Pals, it was the religious centre for the Hindu community. Nawada tourism is something that one would cherish for the hamlets full of temples. It also possesses eye cathcing natural beauty. Talking about the places that can be toured in Nawada are Sobhnath, Gunawa Jal temple and Sankat Mochan mandir which are the most popular religious spots over here. For Jain community, Nawada holds a special interest because the place has spiritually rich in Jainism because of the places like Gunawa temple, Pawanpuri Tirthankar. The popular element of Nawada tourism is Kakolat waterfalls that originate from Kakolat hills. This tourist place has got wonderful surroundings to visit and this is one place that no tourist would wish to miss upon. As per the beliefs, Lord Krishna used to come with his queens to take bath here. The other popular destinations are Narad museum and Rajauli known for scenic beauty. Nawada tourism allures you as the festivals of Nawada include gala celebration of Mahavir Jayanti, Janmashtmi and Chatt puja. As far as the weather of Nawada is concerned, the summers are very hot and winters are chilly and monsoons are heavy. The best time to enjoy Nawada tourism is from September to March but people do plan an outing to this place in summers to enjoy the beauty of Kakolat hills.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Good accommodation facilities are available across major points of Nawada. Staying in luxury hotels will save from incurring hefty costs while best amenities are offered at nominal rates. Tourists can enjoy a perfect stay in Nawada because several hotels and lodges offer best amenities at affordable prices.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Gaya Airport is the nearest airport, which is about 61.8 kms away from Nawada. Tourists can reach various parts of the city from the airport after hiring metered taxis for a reasonable fare.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Bihar Sharif Railway Station about 36 kms is the nearest railway station to reach Nawada. Private cabs and non metered autos are available to and from the station to reach various parts of the city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Bihar Bus Stand about 1.4 kms is the nearest bus stand to reach Nawada. BSRTC buses regularly ply on this route.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Nawada can be easily reached through the road networks existing in the city. National Highway 31 passes through the city which connects it to various other major cities within the state.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - MAA TARA FAST FOOD, LOCATED AT NARDIGANJ ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR CHILLI PRATHA ,CHICKEN ROLL)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - GAURAV SWEET TAPESHWAR JI, LOCATED AT OLD KACHAHARI RD - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA &nbsp;AND GULAB JAMUN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - LADDU GOPAL FAST FOOD CORNER, LOCATED AT SABJI MARKET ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR EGG ROLL AND CHOWMEN)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(607, 14, 31, 734, 'Bihar', 'INDIA', 'PURNIA', 'bicycle-248960_640.jpg', 'bicycle-248960_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Purnia, located in Bihar, owes its name to its oldest temple of Mata Puran Devi. Durga Puja at uniquely designed Ramakrishna Mission at Purnia is very famous. Purnia is famous for spirituality and Sufism. Darghah of Hazrat Mustafa Jamalul Haque Bandagi, Chimni Baza is also located in this city. The Dargah is responsible for the noble work of spreading education, culture and secularism. Purnia an agriculturally blessed land has rich alluvial land owing to number of rivers flowing through it. The major rivers are the Mahananda, the Koli, the Kosi, the Suwara, and the Panar. The rivers also add to the natural beauty of the place. The greenery attracts the tourists as well as the commoners. Tourists could also enjoy some site seeing at the monument anciently known as Kala Bhawan. It still holds the remnants of its King Raja Kalanand Singh and the successors still inhibit the place.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>There are very few guest houses available in the city with basic facilities only.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Malda Airport about 105 kms is the closest airport to Purnia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Purnia has its own junction which connects it to all major cities as well as neighbouring states.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - State Highways 62, 65 and 77 and National Highways NH 31, NH 57 and NH 107 connect neighbouring states and cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Buses are frequently available from all nearby places. So, one can access Purnia easily.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - PURNIA - {FAMOUS FOR KADHI BARI IS A FRIED DUMPLING IN YOGHURT GRAVY ; THEKUA IS A DESERT MADE FROM WHEAT FLOUR, SUGAR SYRUP OR JAGGERY, GHEE AND CARDAMOM}&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - VATIKA FAMILY RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT NH-107, SHIVAJI COLONY - {FAMOUS FOR POTATO(ALOO) DAM AND FRIED CHICKEN}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - 4 LI FAST FOOD AND SWEET CORNER, LOCATED AT RANGBHUMI MAIDAN, MADHUBANI - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA, KACHORI, MOMOS, EGG ROLL, BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - GOKUL SWEET SHOP, LOCATED AT BHATTA BAZAR - (FAMOUS FOR GULABJAMUN, RASAGULLA RASAMALAI)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(608, 14, 31, 734, 'Bihar', 'INDIA', 'ROHTAS', 'plumeria-rubra-344063_1280.jpg', 'plumeria-rubra-344063_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Historically, Rohtas district of Bihar is was a part of Magadh Empire from 6th century BC to 5th century BC under the reign of pre-mauryans. There is a small rock edict of Emperor Ashok suggestive of the Mauryan rule over this place. The 1857 mutiny produced great upheavals in Rohtas. After India attained independence, Rohats became an independent district in 1972 after being a part of Shahbad district. The places which are the charm of Rohtas tourism are Rohtasgarh Fort which is a praiseworthy piece of art that can be attributed the Mughal times of architecture, Tarachandi, which boasts of a beautiful temple, Sasaram which is home to the exquisite tomb of Sher Shah Suri, Shergarh fort built by Hasan Shah sur. Apart from the richness of historical monuments, Rohtasgarh has got significant religious destinations too. Rohtasgarh has got few temples and a masjid. There is Chacha Fagumal Shahibjee ka Gurudwara which is a holy place. Other tourist destinations include Akbarpur, Rehal, Deo Markandey, Bhaluni Dam, Akhorigola and Dhruwan Kund and Gupta Dam. The Rohtas tourism is absolutely extravagant in terms of the places here. The weather conditions of Rohtas are favourable for touring in the months from October to May as the climate is typical of North Indian plains. The vivacity and joy of the people in Rohtas is worth watching when they celebrate their festivals. Rohtas like any place in Bihar celebrates Chath puja on grand scale.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Quality accommodation is available in Rohtas. Staying in luxury hotels will save money with good amenities offered at economical rates. Tourists can enjoy a good stay in the budget hotels that are known to offer best facilities with the best hospitality standards.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Lok Nayak Jayaprakash International Airport in Patna is the nearest airport to reach Rohtas city. Patna is well connected with Mumbai offering more comfort for tourists.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Aurangabad Railway Station is the nearest railway station to reach Rohtas. Metered taxis are available on hire for a cheaper price.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Danwar Bus Stand is at a distance of 5.6 kms from Rohtas city. Govt. owned BSRTC bus services are available on a regular basis to and fro.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Rohtas is well connected with other cities within Bihar such as Patna, Sasaram and Gaya. Private cabs, non metered auto rickshaws and state transport buses connect various centres of Bihar to Rohtas, which is on National Highway 2C.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SAI TARAWAT KENDRA,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT CHOWK BAZAR ROAD, HETIMPUR, NOORAN GANJ, SASARAM - {FAMOUS FOR MASALA DOSA AND BUTTERMILK(LASSI)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - SRI RAM MISTHAN BHANDAR, LOCATED AT PALI RD, GANDHI NAGAR, DEHRI-ON-SONE - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSAS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - GREEN PLANNET EXPRESS RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT NEAR MICO, GT ROAD, DILIA, SASARAM - (FAMOUS FOR BURGERS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - TAJ RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT 1, NATIONAL HIGHWAY 8E, KHILANGANJ, LAXKARIGANJ, SONGADH&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;- (FAMOUS FOR KEBABS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - VRINDAVAN SWEETS &amp; RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT MAHAMAYA COMPLEX,SHEOSAGAR,BIHAR, SH 67, DELHI - KOLKATA HWY, SHIVSAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR RASMALAI AND SOUTH INDIAN DISH)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - DEEPAK FAST FOOD CORNER, LOCATED AT MISHRIPUR ROAD, MOHADDIGANJ - (FAMOUS FOR EGG ROLLS)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(609, 14, 31, 734, 'Bihar', 'INDIA', 'SAHARSA', 'child-with-calf-724803_640.jpg', 'child-with-calf-724803_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Saharsa is a city and a municipality located towards the east of the Kosi River in the Saharsa district of Bihar state. It serves as the administrative headquarters of the Saharsa district, and falls under the Kosi division. Saharsa is located at an average elevation of 41 mts above sea level. The city of Saharsa and its surrounding areas are situated on a flat alluvial plain which had resulted in the formation of the Kosi River basin. The region of Saharsa boasts of being the largest exporter of Makhana in the region as well as the largest producer of bricks making in the entire Kosi. It also offers a few tourist attractions which include several places of historical significance to explore. Most of the attractions constructed here reflect the rich past of the region. A majority of the religious places of interest are scattered around the district region. A large amount of influx of tourists every year has made the authorities to work harder to promote tourism here in a big way. The areas of Kahra and Bangaon have been instrumental towards the whole sectored development of Saharsa. The nearest big town to Saharsa is Patna at a distance of 248 kms.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Saharsa is the city where perfect accommodation facilities are provided even in budget hotels. Tourists can look for luxury amenities in certain 3 start hotels as well. It is better to book hotels before beginning the journey to avoid last minute travails.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Lok Nayak Jayaprakash Narayan International Airport about 248 kms at Khojpura, Patna is the nearest airport to reach Saharsa. Tourists can hire local cabs from the airport for a reasonable fare to reach any part of Saharsa city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Saharsa Railway Station is well linked to Patna and Madhepura. Earlier, there was only a meter gauge line, but in 2006, a much awaited broad gauge line established connection with Khagaria on the New Delhi Guwahati main line.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Saharsa has its own bus stand located at bus stand road where tourists can hire Govt. run BSRTC buses on a regular basis. Saharsa is well connected to all major cities in Bihar State.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Saharsa is connected to Madhepura, Supaul, Khagariya and Patna. It is near National Highway 107, which connects Purnea to Maheshkhunt. State Highway 66 too runs through Saharsa city connecting it with other important cities within the state.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - CHULHA CHOWKA, FAST FOOD CENTRE, LOCATED AT HATIA GACHHI RD, HATIYA GACHHI - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN ROLL)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - GANESH TEA STALL, LOCATED AT SAHARSA-AGWANPUR-BIHRA RD, POLICE LINE - {FAMOUS FOR MIX SPRINKLE (BHUJJA) PAKORI, &nbsp;GULAB JAMUN}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - SRI KRISHNA KANHAIYA VAISHNAV, LOCATED AT POLICE LINE - (FAMOUS FOR CHAT SAMOSA AND KACHORI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - SILKY BREAKFAST, LOCATED AT DB RD, NAYA BAZAR - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;ICE CREAM)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - RAJU, LOCATED AT DB RD, POLICE LINE - {FAMOUS FOR DAL(LENTILS) FRY AND RICE}</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(610, 14, 31, 734, 'Bihar', 'INDIA', 'SAMASTIPUR', 'mangroves-1225680_1280.jpg', 'mangroves-1225680_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Samastipur city of Bihar was earlier a sub-division of Darbhanga district and is situated along the banks of Budhi Gandak River. The major awaited festivals of Samastipur are Chhat, Hanuman Jayanti, Eid, Mohrram, Durga pooja, Diwali and Saraswati pooja. The Pusa block in Samastipur is renowned for its Rajendra Agriculture University. Other important research facilities include Central Tobacco Research Institute and Central Cane Research Institute. The city is the birthplace of many well-known freedom fighters. It is worth mentioning that the city is an important centre for industries as there are many small scale and large industries set up. His place has absolutely no forest cover and hence people depend heavily on agriculture and they are known for their hard working nature. Samastipur tourism can be enjoyed for the richness of fruits like mangoes and litchis that grow here. The place also excels in the commercial arena by producing cash crops like tobacco, cane, chilli, turmeric and different types of vegetables like cauliflower, potato, bitter gourd etc. Samastipur tourism is also popular because of the beautiful rivers flowing through the district. People also get attracted to the city to see the two sugarcane factories, one located in Magardahi ghat and the other located in Hasanpur. The climate of Samastipur is divided into Summer Monsoon and winter. The best time to visit Samastipur is from October to March when the climate of the place is quite at ease for the tourists to make the visit.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Good accommodation facilities are available across major points of Smastipur. Staying in luxury hotels will save tourist from incurring hefty costs while best amenities are offered at nominal rates. Tourists can enjoy a perfect stay in Samastipur because of several hotels and lodges offer best amenities at affordable prices.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Samastipur does not have an airport of its own and visitors travelling by air would have to arrive at Jaiprakash Narayan International Airport, Patna which is the nearest airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Samastipur is well connected to New Delhi, Howrah, Mumbai, Patna, Lucknow, Ranchi and all major cities by a formidable network of trains running through India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Samastipur is connected by decent roads. It can be accessed through state highways. Samastipur is connected with National Highway 28.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - State or private buses are frequently available from all nearby cities in the state. So, one can reach here without any problem.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - RAJASTHAN SWEETS, LOCATED AT GUDARI BAZAR - (FAMOUS FOR CHAT,PAW BHAJI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - LADDULAL SWEETS, LOCATED AT MARWARI BAZAR, GUDARI BAZAR - (FAMOUS FOR DOSA AND SWEETS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - RAM SEVAK SWEETS, LOCATED AT SARAIRANJAN - PATORI RD, TARA DHAMAUN - (FAMOUS FOR PANEER CHILLY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - BAKER&#39;S VILLE, LOCATED AT KASHIPUR RD, VEER KUNWAR SINGH COLONY, KASIPUR - (FAMOUS FOR CAKES)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(611, 14, 31, 734, 'Bihar', 'INDIA', 'SHEIKHPURA', 'lily-1672139_640.jpg', 'lily-1672139_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Sheikhpura is a city and a municipality in Sheikhpura district in the Indian state of Bihar. Sheikhpura is also an administrative district in the state of Bihar in India. The district occupies an area of 689 sq kms. There are a number of exciting things to do in Sheikhpura. From historical sites to cultural attractions, explore the exhaustive list of all other local attractions in Sheikhpura. Sheikhpura district is one of the thirty eight districts of Bihar state, and Sheikhpura town is the administrative headquarters of this district. Sheikhpura district is a part of Munger Division. Sheikhpura was separated from Munger district and was made a separate district with headquarters at Sheikhpura on 31 July 1994. Sheikhpura district has given many veteran leaders to the nation like the first chief minister of Bihar, Shri Krishna Singh, Sukhdev Prasad Singh, Member of Parliyament Rajo Singh etc. The main role in the formation of this district was of Rajo Singh.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Tourists prefer to stay at Rajgir. There are a number of moderately priced hotels available at Rajgir. Tourists can stay at any of the three Tourists Bungalows of Bihar State Tourism Development Corporation Ltd.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport is Lok Nayak Jayaprakash Airport, Patna. Domestic flights to major Indian cities are available from there.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Nearest Railway station to Sheikhpura is Sheikhpura Railway Station. Sheikhpura is located on the broad gauge line Gaya Kiul line connecting Kiul and Gaya.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Nearest Bus stand to Sheikhpura is Bihar Sharif Bus Stand. The town is connected by road to major hubs in the region with frequent bus service.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - VAMIKA VIHAR, LOCATED AT JAWAHAR LAL NEHRU MARG, KHOJPURA, MALI TOLA - {FAMOUS FOR NAAN(ROTI) WITH PANEER}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - SHITAL CHHAYA, LOCATED AT BARBIGHA MARKET RD, ONAMA, BARBIGHA - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA, PASTRIES AND CAKE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - ROUTE 14, LOCATED AT PAVITRA MARKET, RAJABAJAR, BAILEY ROAD, JAWAHAR LAL NEHRU MARG - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN BIRYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - PANKAJ FAST FOOD, LOCATED AT JAMUAWAN - (FAMOUS FOR EGG ROLLS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - ROTI FOOD COURT, LOCATED AT PAVITRA COMPLEX, NEAR MANGAL MARKET, BAILY RD, RAJA BAZAR - (FAMOUS FOR BUTTER PANEER TIKKA MASALA)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(612, 14, 31, 734, 'Bihar', 'INDIA', 'SITAMARHI', 'DA7.jpg', 'DA8.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Sitamarhi is a historical town which serves as the district headquarters of Sitamarhi district, in the northern part of Bihar. The city is located at an average elevation of 56 mts above sea level. Geographically, the region is drained by rivers like Baghmati, Aghwara, Lakhandei, Manusmara &amp; some other small streams. The northern part of Sitamarhi falls under the foothills of Himalaya Mountains. The name Sitamarhi has been derived from the term Sitamahi, which literally translates to Hermitage of Sita. As per Hindu mythology and the epic Ramayana, it is the birthplace of Sita and even represented as the spiritual centre for many seers and pilgrims. The Janaki temple was constructed in her devotion. Sitamarhi has to it&rsquo;s aboard many religious and historical spots. The pilgrimage tourism in particular has over the years attracted many devotees. The pilgrim places mark some of the most important events in the history of Indian religion. Legends even have it that Draupadi the wife of Pandavas was also born here. The culture of Sitamarhi is rich in folk arts, dance and music. The lac bangles of the place are also quite popular. The world renowned Madhubani paintings are done in several blocks of this district. The Jat Jatni and Jhinjhari are the popular folk dances of the Sitamarhi district. Sitamarhi also offers a large number of religious, historic and modern tourist attractions.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Good decent accommodation facilities are available across major points of Sitamarhi. Staying in luxury hotels will save from incurring hefty costs while best amenities are offered at nominal rates. Tourists can enjoy a perfect stay in the several budget hotels and lodges that Sitamarhi offers.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Lok Nayak Jayaprakash Narayan Airport at Khojpura, Patna is the nearest airport to Sitamarhi. Patna is well connected by air to rest of the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Sitamarhi railway station lies on the Raxaul Darbhanga rail route in the eastern central railway zone. Only a few selected trains stop at this station. The nearest major railhead is at Muzaffarpur Junction which is at 54 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Sitamarhi (Dumra bus stand) is well connected to all cities in &amp; around Bihar by state owned BSRTC and local bus services. Some private deluxe buses also ply on a regular basis between Patna and Sitamarhi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - From Sitamarhi, major cities can be easily reached through National Highway 77 and National Highway 104.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - RFC RESTAURANT SITAMARHI, LOCATED AT SHRI RAM COMPLEX, RING BANDH, MATHURA HIGH SCHOOL ROAD, LAXMANA NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR CHIKEN BIRYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - KRISHNA SWEETS, LOCATED AT SHARIF COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA CHAT)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - PRABHAT MISTHAN, LOCATED AT GOVT BUS STAND RUNNISAIDPUR NEAR, NH 77 - (FAMOUS FOR BALUSHAHI IS A SWEET DESERT)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - LADDU GOPAL SWEET SHOP, LOCATED AT LAXMANA NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR CHOWMEEN AND CHOLLE BHATURE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - SITAMARHI - {FAMOUS FOR MUDHI KACHDI IS A SNACK (MUDHI IS PUFFED RICE) AND (KACHDI&rsquo;S MAIN INGREDIENTS ARE BESAN AND PYAJ)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(613, 14, 31, 734, 'Bihar', 'INDIA', 'SIWAN', 'blue-mormon-179183_640.jpg', 'blue-mormon-179183_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Siwan district is one of the districts of Bihar state. Siwan town is the administrative head quarters of this district. Siwan district is a part of Saran division since 1972. The town is known for its great past especially for First President of Indian Republic Dr. Rajendra Prasad who belonged to Jeeradei. The district is also known as Aliganj Sawan after the name of Ali Bux. Siwan has historical and mythological importance attached to it. Siwan, situated in the western part of the State, was originally a sub division of Saran district, which in ancient days formed a part of Kosala Kingdom. The district is bounded on the east by the Saran district, on the north by Gopalganj district and on the west and south by two districts of U.P. viz. Deoria and Balia respectively. Siwan is known for its ancient temples. A large number of devotees assemble at Mehdat temple or Anand Bagh Math and Sunder Bagh Math. People also gather at Faridpur to have a glimpse of Ashiana, the house of Maulana Mazharul Haq, an eminent Bihari who stood for Hindu Muslim unity. Siwan derived its name from Shiva Man, a Bandh Raja whose heirs ruled this area till Babar&rsquo;s arrival. Maharajganj, which is another subdivision of Siwan district, may have found its name from the seat of the Maharaja there.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Multiple hotels from all ranges are available in Siwan for tourist accommodation.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Siwan is connected with Hajipur, Saran and Gopalganj. The district is not connected by any state highway. But then also it is connected through some important metalled roads which serve as the important route for transport.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- The district is connected through railways. Siwan is an important railway station of the Northern Eastern Railway as over here main traffic of sugar and vegetable are dealt.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport is Lok Nayak Jayaprakash Airport in Patna at about 144 kms from Siwan.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SIWAN - {FAMOUS FOR GHUGNI IS A SNACK MADE FROM BLACK GRAM OR DRIED YELLOW PEAS OR WHITE PEAS, AND GRAVY, SERVED WITH PUFFED RICE ; PITHA IS A TYPE OF CAKE MADE FROM RICE FLOUR OR WHEAT FLOUR ; PUA, IS A SWEET DISH PREPARED &nbsp;WITH POWDERED RICE, SUGAR, MILK, HONEY AND GHEE DURING CEREMONY OR PUJA ; MAKHANA IS A DISH &nbsp;WHICH IS MIXED WITH SUGAR AND MILK}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - GYPSY CAFE, LOCATED AT SHANTI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - SHANKAR, LOCATED AT CHHAPRA, GOPALGANJ ROAD, PAL NAGAR, ATARSUA - (FAMOUS FOR GULAB JAMUN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - VANSI-VIHAR, LOCATED AT MOULESHRI CHOWK, KASERA TOLI RD, PROFESSOR COLONY, NAYA QUILLA - (FAMOUS FOR DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - FOOD POLITICS, LOCATED AT ANDAR ROAD, AHSAN MARKET, RAMRAJ MORE, NEAR VISHAL MEGA MART, PURANA QUILLA, KAGZI MUHALLA - (FAMOUS FOR SOUPS AND CHICKEN ROLL)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - ASHWANI, LOCATED AT J P CHOWK BUS STOP, SH47, NAYA BAZAR, KAGZI MUHALLA - (FAMOUS FOR SIKH KABAB)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(614, 14, 31, 734, 'Bihar', 'INDIA', 'WEST CHAMPARAN', 'western-ghats-385315_640.jpg', 'western-ghats-385315_1920.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">West Champaran, an administrative district of the state of Bihar offers in itself a great variety of tourist attractions. Nature&rsquo;s scenic splendour can be seen in its lush green forests and highly fertile plains. A wide variety of wild animals and birds proudly call the region their home seeking shelter in the thick forests and wildlife sanctuary. West Champaran tourism offers its visitors the choice of exploring the quaint beauty that is spread over the entire expanse of the district. West Champaran has also been through an eminent passage through the hands of time making its heritage a gem in the tourism of the region. The most comfortable months are that of October to March when travelling around the city can be pleasurable and delightful. Located in the state of Bihar, West Champaran is an exquisite tourist destination and is a historical district which has witnessed several movements in the times of yore. The district is famous for sharing its border with Nepal. It was the key transit centre for weapons in between India and Nepal. Bettiah is the administrative headquarters of the district and is presently a part of the Red Corridor. The district is divided into three sub divisions: Bettiah, Narkatiaganj and Bagaha. West Champaran district was carved out of the old Champaran District in the year 1972 as a consequence of re-organization of the district in the state. The name Champaran is a form of Champaka aranya, a name which can be traced back to the time when the district was a zone of the forest of Champa trees as well as the residence of single ascetics.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are a lot of medium to budget accommodation options nearby West Champaran district. There are medium to budget accommodation options that have all high class facilities like internet, homely food etc.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The Patna Airport is the nearest airport to this city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - It has its own Railway Station named as West Champaran Railway Station which is connected to all the major cities of Bihar. This district has one major railway junction called the Narkatiaganj Junction, along with several other smaller junctions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- West Champaran is connected by the Nation Highway 28 B to major destinations.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - RUCHI RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT VALMIKI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR CHILLI PANEER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - FOOD JUNCTION, LOCATED AT KAMALNATH NAGAR, BETTIAH - (FAMOUS FOR MILKSHAKES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - SARVAN JI CHAT HOUSE, LOCATED AT RAJ COMPOUND, LAL BAZAR, BETTIAH - (FAMOUS FOR DAHI(CURD) BADA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - PRAMODH, LOCATED AT NONEADIH, RAXAUL - (FAMOUS FOR PAAV BHAJI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - MADHUMILAN SWEET, LOCATED AT KUCHAIKOTE - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA AND CHOLLA)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(615, 17, 46, 0, '', 'Brazil', 'RIO DE JANEIRO', 'rio-de-janeiro-809756_640.jpg', 'rio-de-janeiro-809756_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The bustling city of Rio de Janeiro has been one of Brazil&rsquo;s most popular and frequented tourist destinations for decades. Its vibrant city centre is bursting with culture and pulsating with a deep sense of history and heritage. Rio, as it is commonly known, is the second largest city in Brazil and the third largest metropolis in the whole of South America. It is the most visited city in the Southern Hemisphere, which is no mean feat. This makes for an impressive, memorable attraction for visitors from all over the world. Rio de Janeiro is hot for most of the year, and rain is frequent during the period between December and March. Because of its many cultural and historical attractions, Rio has implemented fabulous infrastructure to cater to the needs of its visitors. This includes world-class accommodation and plenty of tours. Major efforts have been made to minimise social inequality and modernise the economy of Rio de Janeiro to further improve its global standing. This makes for a very special destination. Laze on the shores of Ipanema Beach or one of the many other beaches for which this city is renowned. Marvel at the sheer scale of the statue of Christ the Redeemer as it overlooks the city far below. Take the cable car up Sugarloaf Mountain for spectacular views. Stroll down the famous Avenue Nossa Senhora de Copacabana. Take an official walking tour of Rio, learning fascinating facts about its historical and modern day heritage.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Rio de Janeiro offers a wide selection of hotels in Rio de Janeiro as well as hotels in surrounding areas, ranging from 1 to 5 star luxury hotels which can cater for all types of travellers whether it is for business or pleasure. The moderately priced hotel here is a great choice for families. It is quite popular and comes highly recommended. Close to the beach, inexpensive and quite charming these hotels are definitely worth considering while going to Rio de Janerio.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - &nbsp;Galeao Antonio Carlos Jobim International Airport serves the city for both international flights. If coming from within Brazil tourists might get flights from all major cities to Santos Dumas Airport. Airport Transfers have standard pre-decided rates and are a good option.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Rodoviaria Novo Rio is Rio&#39;s central bus station that serves major towns and cities across Brazil and also offers routes to other neighbouring South American countries of Argentina, Chile, Paraguay and Bolivia. The bus company Green Toad Bus offers the service to book tickets online. Other major bus companies that operate out of Rodovi&aacute;ria Novo Rio are Expresso Brasileiro, Express Northeast, Express South, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Rio de Janeiro&#39;s central train station is Central do Brasil, but it only serves the local commuter rail. A high speed rail connection between Rio de Janeiro and Sao Paulo is still underway.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around Rio</strong> -&nbsp;<br />\r\na). By Bus: Busses are the most important means of transportation for exploring all tourist places in Rio de Janeiro. Public transportation in Rio de Janeiro is frequent and cheap.<br />\r\nb). Other Public transport: Other forms of public transport like metros are slowly gaining momentum. Tourists may not find them everywhere but they are worth considering.<br />\r\nc). Drive: Driving around is not the best option. Remember that the city is quite crowded and there is constant traffic jams so parking and driving tend to be a bit of a pain.<br />\r\nd). Cycling: Cycling is a decent option as one can hire a bike, and there are plenty of cycle tracks around the city. The destination can be explored on bike fairly easily and makes a way to sightsee the city to its fullest.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - RIO DE JANEIRO - [FAMOUS FOR FEIJOADA IS ASTEW OF BEANS MADE WITH BEEF AND PORK MEAT ; CHURRASCO &nbsp;IS A GRILLED MEAT DISH MADE FROM CHICKEN AND PORK ; ACARAJE IS A DISH MADE FROM BEANS, PEPPER, GROUND BLACK-EYED-PEAS AND ONIONS ; SIRI CASQUINHA IS A MEAT DISH MADE FROM CHOPPED CRAB MEAT AND SERVED WITH GREEN SAUCE ; LEAO VELSO SOUP MADE FROM &nbsp;SHRIMP HEAD AND LOBSTER &nbsp;MEATY FISH AS WELL AS FRIED ONION, TOMATO AND SAFFRON ; &nbsp;MOQUECA BASED ON SHRIMP OR FISH STEW WITH COCONUT MILK, ONIONS, GARLIC, TOMATOES AND CILANTRO ; PAO DE QUEIJO IS A SNACK AND BREAKFAST FOOD MADE FROM YUCCA FLOUR AND SEVERAL CHEESE ; KIBBEH IS ADISH MADE OF BULGUR, MINCED ONIONS, LEAN BEEF,LAMB, GOAT OR CAMEL MEAT WITH SPICES ; COXINHAS IS A SNACK MADE OF SOY ; CAIPIRINHA IS A ALCOHOLIC BEVERAGE MADE WITH CACHACA, SUGAR AND LIME]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - X-TUDO, AT R. TRES, 35 - INHOAIBA - [FAMOUS FOR BURGERS]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - CULTIVAR, AT RUA PASCHOAL CARLOS MAGNO, 124 - SANTA TERESA - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;PAO DE QUEIJO]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - ACARAJE DA NEGA TERESA, LOCATED NEXT TO POPULAR LOCAL HANGOUT BAR DO BONDE - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;PATTIES]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - CHICO E ALAIDE, AT RUA DIAS FERREIRA, 679 LEBLON - [FAMOUS FOR ESCONDIDINHO]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - PAVAO AZUL, AT RUA HILARIO DE GOUVEIA, 71 COPACABANA - [FAMOUS FOR BOLINHO DE BACALHAU IS A COD CAKE MIXED WITH FLOUR AND EGG YOLKS]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - CERVANTES, AT AVENIDA PRADO JUNIOR, 335 LOJA B COPACABANA - [FAMOUS FOR PINEAPPALE SANDWICH]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>8 - SABOR D.O.C., AT RUA DIAS FERREIRA, 605 LEBLON - [FAMOUS FOR ESPETINHO]</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(616, 14, 31, 745, 'Maharashtra', 'INDIA', 'AHMEDNAGAR', 'rice-farm-1946224_1280.jpg', 'rice-farm-1946224_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Ahmednagar is a city in the Ahmednagar district that comes under the state of Maharashtra. Lying on the west bank of the river Sina, the Ahmednagar district by itself is the largest district in Maharashtra. Ahmednagar is located centrally in Maharashtra and hence is equidistant from Pune and Aurangabad. Aurangabad falls to its north alongside Nashik, while Pune lies to its south along with the district of Sholapur. The east side sees the Beed and Osmanabad district while Thane lies on the west side. Ahmednagar has a track record of more than a half a millennium worth of history, starting right back in the 1490s. Ahmednagar was established as a town back in 1494 by the Ahmed Nizam Shah. The district hence derives its name from its founder. The region&rsquo;s history goes right back to the time when Ahmed Nizam Shah founded the district under the Nizami Shahi dynasty right before it was taken over by the great Mughal ruler, Shah Jahan, around 150 years later in 1636. Ahmednagar later went on to the Peshwas and the Maratha, in and around 1759 post which it was handed over to Daulat Rao Sindhia the Maratha Chief. The British, under the leadership of Lord Wellesley, were the last of its conquerors, when Ahmednagar came as per the Treaty of Poona in 1817. The last of the great lineage of rulers of the Mughal Empire, Aurangzeb spent his last years in this very place. A small monument in Ahmednagar commemorates his noteworthy reign over the region. The Ahmednagar Fort is one of the major attractions in the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There is plenty of staying accommodation in Ahmednagar. Visitors can avail Deluxe, First Class, Economy, Budget; Government approved hotels, lodges and guest houses.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- The Pune Lohegaon Airport is the nearest domestic airport to Ahmednagar, at a distance of about 113 kms. The Chattrapati Shivaji Airport in Mumbai is the nearest International Airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Ahmednagar is well connected by road to most of the cities within the state and neighbouring states.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Ahmednagar is well connected by rail to all the major towns and cities within and outside Maharashtra. There are regular daily trains from Shirdi, Mumbai, Pune, and many more cities to help you reach Ahmednagar comfortably.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Ahmednagar is well connected to all parts of the state by private luxury buses as well as government run state bus services.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - &nbsp;AHMEDNAGAR - [FAMOUS FOR HOT-MASALA-MILK ; BHINGAR IS A TOWN (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;NON VEGETARIAN FOOD) ; MATKI BHEL ; MODAK IS A SWEET DISH PREPARED DURING GANESH CHATURTHI ; PURAN POLI IS &nbsp;A SWEET FLAT FLAT BREAD IS A SWEET FLAT BREAD PREPARED FROM WHEAT, SUGAR AND YELLOW GRAM ; SHIRKHAND IS A SWEET DISH MADE FROM YOGURT, SUGAR, CARDAMOM AND SAFFRON ; SHEERA IS BREAKFAST INDIAN DESSERTS MADE FROM SEMOLINA, SUGAR, GHEE AND MILK]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - DURGASING, IN AHMEDNAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR LASSI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - BOMBAY SWEETS, IN AHMEDNAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR RABDI-BASUNDI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - ZOPDI CANTEEN, IN AHMEDNAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR COFFEE AND SANDWITICHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - RASARANG, IN AHMEDNAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR PAV)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - GOLI VADA PAV - (FAMOUS FOR PAV BHAJI)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(617, 14, 31, 745, 'Maharashtra', 'INDIA', 'AKOLA', 'bird-2053035_1280.jpg', 'bird-2053035_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Akola is prominent city cum district that lies in the western parts of the Nagpur Division of Maharashtra State and is surrounded by Amravati district in the north and northeast, Yavatmal in the southeast, Washim in the south and Buldhana in the west. The two main rivers of the district are the Purna and the Penganga, the other less important rivers being the tributaries of these two rivers. The name of Akola is derived from the name of The Great Warrior King Akol Singh. The city of Akola is located in the north central part of Maharashtra state, western India, on the banks of Murna River and it is an important district in Vidarbha region of Maharashtra State. Although not much of a tourist destination, it still is an important historical, cultural, political, agricultural and industrial city. The place is a prominent road and rail junction in the Tapti River valley which is a commercial trading centre chiefly in cotton. Akola is an important educational centre as well with several colleges affiliated with the University of Nagpur. The place is gradually developing into a great market centre. The main language spoken by the people of Akola is Marathi. Some communities also speak Urdu and Hindi.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Akola city is well equipped with excellent accommodation facilities, which vary from luxurious cottages and hotels. There are some reasonable accommodation options too at the numerous guesthouses and tourist lodges in the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Shivani Airport is the domestic airport of Akola city and has one runway. The airport is just 7 kms away from the city on National Highway 6. The nearest domestic airport is at Nagpur at 250 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Akola is well connected all major cities within the state as well as other Indian states. Akola railway station enjoys Meter as well as Broad gauge systems.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - State owned and private air conditioned bus services run daily to most major cities to and from Akola. The bus frequency is good.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Akola is well connected by road to major cities within the state. The NH 6 runs through Akola from Hajira to Kolkata. NH 6 is a part of Asian Highway 46. Maharashtra state transport buses are most commonly used by people to travel to rural parts of the region.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - AKOLA - [FAMOUS FOR THALIPEETH IS A MULTIGRAIN PANCAKE PREPARED FROM &nbsp;FLOUR (CHANA DAL, URAD DAL, WHEAT, RICE, CORIANDER SEEDS AND CUMIN SEEDS), PAIRED WITH CURD ; KARANJI IS A SWEET SAVORY SNACK OFTEN MADE FOR FESTIVAL LIKE DIWALI AND GANESH CHATURATI ; &nbsp;ANARSA IS A DELICIOUS SWEET WHICH IS OFFERED DURING PUJAS AND FESTIVAL ; TILGUL IS LIKE A &nbsp;SWEET CANDY, DURING ON SANKRANTI(HINDU FESTIVAL) IT IS AMIXTURE OF SESAME SEEDS AND JAGGERY]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - Parcel Food Point, IN AKOLA - (FAMOUS FOR MUTTON KEEMA, CHICKEN AND MASALA EGG BOILED)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - KATA KIRRRRR, IN AKOLA - (FAMOUS FOR MISAL PAV)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(618, 14, 31, 745, 'Maharashtra', 'INDIA', 'BEED', 'bajirao-peshave-statue-76553_640.jpg', 'bajirao-peshave-statue-76553_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Beed also known as Bid is a popular city Beed is a town, which is the administrative headquarters of the Beed district located in the central part of Maharashtra. It is surrounded by Aurangabad and Jalna in the North, Parbhani and Latur in the East, Ahmednagar and Osmanabad in the South and Ahmednagar in the West. Godavari is the most significant river that flows on the borderline of Georai and Majalgaon Tehsils. The origin of the present name of Beed is very ambiguous. Regarding this, there are two different opinions. Bhir is believed to have become Beed with the passage of time. Beed is situated in the Deccan black basalt stone, ranges of Balaghat that constitutes main range from Ahmednagar in the west, to the border of district Beed in the East. The city of Beed is the largest urban area in the district with distinctive climate and pristine treasures. It is a place of historical importance and the place is flooded with historical building that exemplify of the grandeur of the town. As the place was ruled by the famous rulers of medieval era, the culture of the dynasties were also merged with the culture of the city and with the progression of time the city became an amalgamation of the cultural abundance. With a view of rich traditional heritage and religious affluence, tourism in Beed includes a superb nature tour with a lot of places to trip. In addition to that the city stands as the preserver of the mammoth historical creations with the luxury of designs and stone carving. Beed has some religious buildings that cater to the need of the people who want to make pilgrimage tour to the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are various hotels in Beed that provide immense customer satisfaction along with excellent room services. One can enjoy the delightful accommodation of the hotels that offer spending quality time with an addition to the suitability of the pocket.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- The closest domestic airport is Aurangabad about 133 kms, while the nearby international airports are Mumbai about 418 kms and Pune 250 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- The closest railway stations are Vaijnath about 120 kms, Aurangabad about 133 kms and Ahmednagar about 145 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Govt. owned MSRTC and private buses run on a regular basis from Beed to major cities in Maharashtra and neighbouring states.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Beed is well connected by road to major towns in the state. The National highway 211 that runs from Ahmadabad to Hyderabad passes through the town. Maharashtra State Road Transport Corporation buses and some private owned travel agencies offer bus services to the main cities of the state from Beed.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SAGAR, LOCATED AT NATIONAL HIGH WAY 211, SHAHUNAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR PAVV BHAJI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - GOLI, LOCATED AT SHIN VAR PETH, MOMINPURA - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;VADA PAAV AND CHAT ITEMS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - LAZIZ, LOCATED AT MANE COMPLEX, SHOP NO. 7-8 NEAR NA VGAN COLLEGE, DATTA NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - SHI V SHANKAR, LOCATED IN BEED - (FAMOUS FOR PAV BHAJI)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '');
