(619, 14, 31, 745, 'Maharashtra', 'INDIA', 'BHANDARA', 'birds-1777358_640.jpg', 'birds-1777358_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Bhandara is an important administrative district in the State of Maharashtra. The district headquarters are located at Bhandara which is the second major city in Vidharbha region. Geographically, the district lies entirely within the Wainganga basin. Three major tributaries of the Wainganga the Bagh, the Bawanthari and the Chulband drain the district. Bhannara is mentioned in an inscription at Ratanpur about 1100 AD. The current derivation from bhana, a brass dish is based on the fact that the town has a large brass working industry. Bhandara, the district of lakes is the administrative district in the state of Maharashtra. Bhandara district consists of two sub divisions, which are further divided into seven taluks. The city of Bhandara is also known as the Brass City as it has the largest concentration of brass metal production units in India. Another thing, which Bhandara is famous for, is its high quality rice production. More than one third of the area of the district lies under jungle that yields gum, medicinal fruit and nuts, edible fruits. Tourism in Bhandara district comprises visiting a number of places of both religious significance as well as leisure activities. Apart from the ancient temples, the district of Bhandara has a lot of activities to offer the tourists. There are ancient sites and historical monuments. There are some beautiful lakes, parks and sanctuaries as well. When looking for rest and relaxation, the places that Bhandara has to offer its tourists are full of scenic beauty.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Bhandara offers its visitors a decent amount of staying options to choose from. These include budget hotels, lodges and guesthouses to deluxe hotels. MTDC also offers a few good rest houses in most tourist places of Bhandara district.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">By Air - The nearest airport is at Nagpur about 60 kms from Bhandara.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">By Train - Bhandara is connected by rail via broad and narrow gauge line with stations at Bhandara Road and Tumsar Road.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">By Bus - State government public transport buses ply between Bhandara and other cities in the State. Tourist bus services at regular intervals are also available.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">By Road - State highways and roads from the district headquarters at Bhandara link all sub divisions and major towns. National highway 6 passes through the district.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - JAIN RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT NATIONAL HIGH WAY 6, &nbsp;VIDARBHA HOUSING BOARD COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - MALHAR FRESH, LOCATED AT STATION ROAD, NEAR HUTATMA GARDEN, SHASTRINAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR CAKES, PASTRIES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - B P DA DHABA, LOCATED AT BHANDARA - (FAMOUS FOR ONION PAKODA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - SAI BABA RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT BHANDARA RD, SAI COLONY, TUMSAR - {FAMOUS FOR DAHI(CURD)-SAMOSA}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - THE CAFE, LOCATED AT J. M. PATEL COLLEGE RD, MSEB COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR ALOO TIKKI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - RAMDAS, LOCATED IN BHANDARA - (FAMOUS FOR POHA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - KAMBOJ FOODS, LOCATED AT &nbsp;VIDARBHA HOUSING BOARD COLONY, MSEB COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR SOUTH INDIAN FOOD)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(620, 14, 31, 745, 'Maharashtra', 'INDIA', 'BULDHANA', 'sunset-2028653_640.jpg', 'sunset-2028653_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Buldhana district is located in the central portion of the state of Maharashtra. Akola, Jalgaon, Jalna, Parbhani are the adjoining districts to the east, west &amp; south respectively. Buldhana is a city located on the top of a mountain in Ajanta ranges, in central India and is about 900 mts above sea level. The city was named so after the people bhill who lived here earlier. At that time it was called as bhillthana and when British came the name was changed to Buldhana and finally to Buldana. Bounded in the north by the Nirmur district of Madhya Pradesh, in the east by Akola district, in south by Parbhani district and in the west by Aurangabad and Jalgaon district, Buldhana lies partly in the Tapi basin and partly in the Godavari basin. The landscape district of Buldhana is rich and varied with gently sloping fertile riverside plains studded with agriculturally prosperous villages. The place offers lots of tourist attractions as the region is known for its scenic beauty and charming atmosphere. An added attraction of the area of Buldhana District is the festivals where travellers can visit the Sarai Mahasiddha Baba fair and Shri Balaji fair. One can buy wide range of local handicrafts and artefacts from the fairs. One can also make a trip to the Ajanta caves which are within easy reach from here. Khamgaon and Malkapur are the major cotton trading towns in the district.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Although Buldhana offers limited staying options, one can find accommodation easily in Buldhana. One can choose from guest houses, lodges and hotels in Buldhana at moderate rates. Most of them are located close to the main town centre.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport is at Aurangabad which is 135 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- There is no railway station in Buldhana. So one can book the railway tickets from Buldhana railway reservation centre and can travel from nearest railway junction like Malkapur, Akola, Bhusawal and Shegaon.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Buldhana is well connected by road and regular govt. and private buses ply from the various cities and neighbouring towns of the state.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - National Highway 6 passes through Khamgaon, Nandura, and Malkapur towns in the district.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - KRUSHANA RESTA, LOCATED AT MH MSH 24, CHAITANYA WADI - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORIS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - CHAITRABAN, LOCATED AT BULDANA - (FAMOUS FOR MAHARASHTRIAN &nbsp;VEGETABLES, BUTTERMILK, BAJRA ROTI AND JO WAR ROTI AND SE V BHAJI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - JAI BHAR VNATH CHAT CENTER, LOCATED AT &nbsp;VYANKETESH NAGAR, ASHTA VINAYAK NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR PANIPURI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - BALAJI RAJSTHAN SWEET, LOCATED AT &nbsp;VYANKETESH NAGAR, ASHTA VINAYAK NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR KAJU KATLI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(621, 14, 31, 745, 'Maharashtra', 'INDIA', 'CHANDRAPUR', 'tiger-1631899_640.jpg', 'tiger-1631899_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Situated on the banks of the Irai River, Chandrapur is nestled beautifully in between the Wardha and the Wainganga River basins. It is located in the state of Maharashtra and is the district headquarters. It is an antique city and attracts a large number of tourists from all over India due to its proximity to the Wildlife Parks and its many wonderful temples. It is also widely famous as the city of Black Gold due to the existence of large number of coal mines. Chandrapur city is extensively known for its Forts and Temples. Mahakali Mandir is one of the prominent tourist attractions of the place. Chandrapur is also admired for its amazingly beautiful Art and Culture. It is famous for the Adivasi, Gondal and Keertam dance forms which is famous worldwide. As per a legend, the name of the place was Lokapura in Krta Yuga. Later on, its name was changed to Indupur during the reign of Raja Chandrahasa. It was then changed to Chandrapur. Gonds ruled Chandrapur in 9th century and in 1854, Chandrapur was formed an independent district. Chandrapur is famous for its super thermal power plant, one of the biggest in Asia, and its vast reserves of coal. Due to large number of coal mines present around the city. One of the most famous tourist attractions located in the district is the Tadoba Andhari Tiger Reserve. The city of Chandrapur has ancient temples of the goddess Mahakali and of Anchaleshwar, a form of the god Shiva.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Chandrapur is well equipped with small budgeted hotels, which offer a comfortable stay at reasonable prices.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Sonegaon Nagpur is the nearest airport to Chandrapur at 150 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Chandrapur has its own railway station and is located on the main New Delhi Chennai railway line of Indian Rail. It comes under Nagpur division of the Central Railway.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- Chandrapur is also connected to many cities in Maharashtra by MSRTC buses. The buses ply to Nagpur, Gondia, Amravati, Akola, Shirdi, Aurangabad, Nanded, and Hyderabad.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Located on major road routes, Chandrapur is well connected with all the places in the state. There are also regular private and government buses from Nagpur to Chandrapur.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: right;"><strong>1 - CHANDRAPUR - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;VHANGYACHA VHARIT IS A TRADITIONAL DISH MADE OF EGGPLANTS, GINGER, ONIONS AND GREEN CHILIES, ANS SERVED WITH CHAPATTI OR BRUNT GARLIC RICE ; MAKAI CHIWADA IS A SNACK PREPARED WITH WHEAT OR MAIZEakai Chiwda, SOMETIMES CORNFLAKES ARE ALSO ADDED ; &nbsp;CHAKLI IS &nbsp;A CRISPY SNACK MADE FROM CHANNA FLOUR, CEREALS AND WATER AND SERVED WITH SPICY CHUTNEYS ; KAANDE POHE IS ABREAKFAST SNACK MIXED WITH SPICES, ONION AND POTATO]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(622, 14, 31, 745, 'Maharashtra', 'INDIA', 'DHULE', 'hill-road-204115_6402.jpg', 'hill-road-204115_6403.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Dhule, also called as Dhulia is a city cum district located in the state of Maharashtra. Lying on the northern tip of Maharashtra, Dhule is the administrative headquarter of the district. The district shares its borders with Nandurbar district lying in the northeast, Nashik in the south and Jalgaon district lies to the east of Dhule district. Historians believe that Dhule was named by Akbar as Dandes after his son Daniyal. Some believe that the city got its name by a famous sage with the same gothra. Dhule city lies in north western part of Maharashtra State. The district of Dhule has one prime river basin the Tapi Basin. Satpuda Hill range lies in the northern part of the district. It is one of the very few well planned cities of India that was created even before Indian Independence. Dhule is a popular stop for truckers, owing to its location on two national highways. The single most reason for importance of Dhule to India and Maharashtra is because of its geographical location for road transport industry. The city was designed by Sir Vishweshwaraya and is renowned for its educational heritage. It hosts a big number of educational institutes. The place has been one of the big centres for textile industry of the nation, with both spinning and weaving operations. Textile industry is still alive here though at much smaller scale as compared to the past. Many small scale industries are shaping up in MIDC area of Dhule.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Dhule has handful of hotels. The budget hotels in Dhule provide clean and spacious accommodation with basic amenities that are required for a pleasant and comfortable stay. At Dhule hotels, tourists can choose from standard rooms, deluxe rooms and several other room categories.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest international airport is Mumbai, though it also has its own domestic airport at Gondur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Dhule also has a distinct railway terminus, which is connected to nearest railway junction at Chalisgaon. Manmad Dhule Indore railway route is about to be started very soon.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- MSRTC and private service buses ply to major cities of Maharashtra state from Dhule.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Dhule is the city where most strategic roads of India criss-cross each other. The national highway 3 virtually connects southern India with northern India. And the national highway 6 on its part connects western India with eastern India.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - AMBIKA MITHAI BHANDAR, IN DHULE - [FAMOUS FOR LADDU, BALUSHAI, PEDA, BARFI AND GATHIYA]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - APNI BAKERY - IN DHULE - (FAMOUS FOR PASTRIES AND KHULCHA NAAN)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(623, 14, 31, 745, 'Maharashtra', 'INDIA', 'GADCHIROLI', 'hibiscus-1760929_1280.jpg', 'hibiscus-1760929_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">The town of Gadchiroli is the administrative headquarters of the district. Gadchiroli is situated in the south eastern corner of Maharashtra State, and is bounded by Chandrapur district to the west, Gondia district to the north, Chhattisgarh state to the east, and Andhra Pradesh state to the south and southwest. Some believe that Gadchiroli derives its name from the Gond kings who ruled the region. Some say that it&#39;s been named after the Godavari River. Gadchiroli is a popular tourist destination in the state of Maharashtra. The district is divided into three different zones based on the type of soil present there. The region of Gadchiroli is known as a tribal belt of the state with hardly any basic amenities. The area still holds a few interesting artistic temple sculptures of which some can be found in Markanda from the ancient times bringing in a fair amount of tourist to this place. Vast regions of Gadchiroli are covered by forests. These forests also have a plethora of flora and fauna. The Chaprala sanctuary is another major tourist attraction. Tourists can visit Gadchiroli to experience a fantastic weekends during the winter. Gadchiroli is situated about 180 kms from Nagpur.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Gadchiroli offers limited staying options for visitors. One can choose from small time budget hotels, guest houses and lodges in and around the city at reasonable prices.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest airport is at Nagpur about 180 kms from Gadchiroli.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Train </strong>- The nearest railway station is at Chandrapur at a distance of 80 kms. Gadchiroli has 18.5 kms of narrow gauge railway lines passing through the north western part of the district.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Govt. run MSRTC buses ply on a regular basis to major cities of the State.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Road</strong> - Although there are no national highways passing through Gadchiroli, roads from the district headquarters at Gadchiroli link all sub-districts and towns of Maharashtra and neighbouring states.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(624, 14, 31, 745, 'Maharashtra', 'INDIA', 'GONDIA', 'flower-1239893_1280.jpg', 'flower-1239893_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Gondia district was carved out by division of Bhandara district. Gondia district is situated on north eastern side of Maharashtra State having state borders of Madhya Pradesh and Chhattisgarh. In ancient time, this region was ruled over by Gond kings. The rich dense forest reflects in the culture of Gond people whose main business at that time was to collect lak from Palas tree and Gum from Babul tree, Gum is called as Gond in Hindi, hence the name. Gondia district is situated along the north eastern part of the state of Maharashtra. It was carved out of the Bhandara district. For administrative purposes the district is divided into two subdivisions namely Gondia and Deori, which are further divided into four taluks. Spread over an area of 5425 sq kms, the region of Gondia is mostly covered with forests. The district is underdeveloped where Paddy is main agriculture produce. There is no large scale industry in the entire district due to this district is economically backward. &nbsp;The city is popularly known as Rice city due to large number of rice mills. Gondia district is not known to be an idyllic tourist destination but still has some outstanding attractions to visit. It also houses some exotic mountain ranges and rural landscape unfettered by civilization. Some of the notable attractions are the 25000 year old natural caves, ancient temples that impart an antique look that has a site of archaeological importance. The Nagzira Sanctuary and Nawegaon National Park are important wildlife destinations.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Gondia offers its visitors a decent amount of staying options to choose from. These include budget hotels, lodges and guesthouses to deluxe hotels. MTDC also offers a few good rest houses in most tourist places of Gondia district.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Gondia Airport is 15 kms from Gondia city situated near Kamtha Village. The other nearest airport is at Nagpur at a distance of 130 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Gondia junction on is on Mumbai Kolkatta route. The station has three platforms out of which two are for broad gauge and the third for narrow gauge railway line.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - State government public transport buses ply between Gondia and other cities in the state. Tourist bus services at regular intervals are also available.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - The city is well connected by roads. National highway 6 is the only national highway that goes through Gondia, which helps in keeping it connected with major cities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1- GONDIA - [FAMOUS FOR PHANAS POLI(FLAT BREAD)MADE OF WHEAT FLOUR WITH ADDED FLOOR OF PHANAS(JACKFRUIT)]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(625, 14, 31, 745, 'Maharashtra', 'INDIA', 'HINGOLI', 'snake-166498_640.jpg', 'snake-166498_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Hingoli is an administrative district in Maharashtra and Hingoli city is its headquarters. Situated on the northern Hingoli part of Marathwada, Hingoli district is bordered by Akola, Yavatmal, Parbhani and Nanded. The Tehsils of Sengaon, Hingoli, Kalmnuri and Aundha are scattered on this hilly tract. The mountain ranges run in an east west direction. Some places of tourist&#39;s importance in and around Hingoli are Nagnath Temple, Mallinath Digambar Jain Temple, Tulajadevi Sansthan and Sant Namdev Sansthan, etc. Hingoli lies in the northern part of Marathwada in the state of Maharashtra. The district is surrounded by Akola and Yavatmal in the North, Parbhani in the West and Nanded in the Southeast. Known as Patthar Pradesh of Balaghat and Satpuda mountain ranges, the city of Hingoli came into existence as a separate district of Maharashtra from the division of Parbhani district on 1st May 1999. Hingoli district is dotted with several tourist attractions. The travellers love to explore the tourist places located in and around the district. The town, being close to the Vidarbha region of Maharashtra, was of crucial strategic importance during the British rule. In the town can still be found the state farm building which was the base for British Army. The district of Hingoli is primarily agricultural. Among the major crops grown here, cotton, jowar, mango, pulses, rice, groundnut etc are the autumnal crops, whereas wheat, jowar, gram etc are the Rabi crops. Aurangabad is 220 kms away.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The city of Hingoli is equipped with decent staying options which include luxurious lodges, economy to budget hotels and guesthouses. MTDC provides 3 double bedded rooms with restaurant facilities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Aurangabad airport is at 220 kms from Hingoli. Nanded can be another option as the domestic airport is just 60 kms from here.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Hingoli Deccan is a railway station on Kacheguda Khandwa Meter Gauge Section of Hyderabad (HYB) Division of South Central Railway. Another nearby Railway Station is Parbhani connected to Delhi, Mumbai, and Hyderabad by direct trains.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Govt. and private buses ply on a regular basis to all neighbouring cities from Hingoli.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- There is also a good network of roads connecting major towns/cities of the state and neighbouring states.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - UDAYDEEP VEG, LOCATED AT OFF, SRP CAMP - (FAMOUS FOR VEGETARIAN DISHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - PAYAL, LOCATED AT DEVDA NAGAR, MOHALLA PALTAN, SIDDHARTH NAGAR - {FAMOUS FOR PAN(MOUTH FRESHNER)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - JAY AMBE BIKANER SWEET MART, LOCATED AT STATE HIGHWAY 148, BALAJI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA &nbsp;AND JALEBI)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(636, 14, 31, 745, 'Maharashtra', 'INDIA', 'JALGAON', 'snake-166498_6402.jpg', 'snake-166498_6403.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Jalgaon is a city of western India which lies to the north of the Maharashtra state in Jalgaon district. Located on the northern Deccan Plateau, Jalgaon lies north of Nashik, bounded in the north by Satpuda range, in South by Ajanta range, in the west by Dhulia district and in the East by Buldhana district. Jalgaon is often known as the Banana capital of India. Though not a famous tourist destination, the place is bounded by several religious temples and cultural establishments. The world famous heritage site Ajanta caves is far near to Jalgaon district making it as one of major International Tourism hub for tourist to reach the Ajanta &amp; Ellora caves. Jalgaon is also one of the world&#39;s largest pulse milling centres. Jalgaon is a noteworthy collection and distribution centre of agricultural goods and agriculture input industry. Jalgaon is nowadays becoming a well trading centre of Maharashtra and a leading producer of sugarcane.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The city of Jalgaon offers decent staying options. Visitors can choose from economy hotels, budget accommodations and lodges at affordable prices.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Aurangabad is the nearest airport about 155 kms. An airport is being constructed at Kusumba approximately 6 kms from the city which would be in operation soon.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Jalgaon railway station is only 25 kms away from Bhusawal. It is a junction on Mumbai and Surat line. Bhusawal is the divisional headquarter of the Central Railway and is junction of Mumbai Delhi and Mumbai Howrah line.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - State transport plies buses to Jalgaon from almost all the important cities of the state.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Jalgaon lies on the National highway 6 that connects the city to Surat and Kolkatta. Taxis and interstate buses ply on a regular basis.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>JALGAON - [FAMOUS FOR VAANGI BHARITAANGI BHARIT IS A POPULAR DISH PREPARED WITH ONIONS AND BEANS ; EGGPLANT BHAJI IS A &nbsp;DISH MADE FROM DICED EGGPLANT, CHILLIES, GRALIC AND FRIED IN OIL]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(637, 14, 31, 745, 'Maharashtra', 'INDIA', 'JALNA', 'bird-1038312_640.jpg', 'bird-1038312_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Jalna is a centrally placed district of Maharashtra located in the northern direction of Marathwada region. Jalna district shares common boundaries with Parbhani and Buldhana on the east, Aurangabad on the west, Jalgaon on the north and Beed on the south. At the desire of a local wealthy Muslim merchant, who is said to have been a great benefactor of the place, it was named as Jalna, from his occupation of Julaha or weaver. The city of Jalna in Maharashtra was formerly a part of the Nizam State and after the Marathwada Mukti Sangram became part of India, as a Tehsil of district Aurangabad. Eventually it got the status of a separate district on 1st May 1982. The northern part of the district lying between the Satmala hills and the central hill range known as Jalna Hills is an unpaid plateau and is drained by the Purna River and its tributaries. The southern part is low land flat area. The Ajanta range, which enters the district at its north western corner acts as a watershed between the Tapi valley on the north and Godavari valley on the south. Known to be more of a site comprising of religious temples, Jalna district covers an area of 7612 sq kms. The district head quarter is at Jalna and well connected to state capital and national capital by broad gauge railway line. The region is well known for its hybrid seed industries, steel re-rolling mills, bidi industry and agro based industries. The district is also known for the highest production of Sweet Lemon in the state.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Jalna city offers decent staying options. One can choose from guest houses, lodges and hotels at moderate rates. Most of them are located close to the main town centre.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Jalna does not have an airport. The nearest airport is at Aurangabad at a distance of 60 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Jalna town is well connected to state capital and national capital by broad gauge railway line. Jalna is connected with Manmad railway junction via Aurangabad and also with Hyderabad on the broad gauge line of Central railway.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Regular govt. and private bus services are available from Jalna to all the important neighbouring towns including Mumbai, Nashik, Manmad, Hyderabad, and Shirdi etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Jalna has excellent road connectivity. Jalna has road connecting to Aurangabad, Pune, Ahmednagar, Nagpur, Beed, and Mumbai which are upgraded into four lane highways. A New Nagpur Aurangabad Mumbai highway passing through Jalna is being developed.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - JALNA - (FAMOUS FOR VADA PAV, PAO BHAAJI AND SAMOSAS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - KALYANI ICE CREAM PARLOUR, IN JALNA - (FAMOUS FOR ,KALA KHATTA, NIMBUPANI, MANGO AND CHOCOLATE SHAKES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - COFFEE HOUSE, IN JALNA - (FAMOUS FOR HOT AND COKD COFFEE)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(638, 14, 31, 745, 'Maharashtra', 'INDIA', 'KOLHAPUR', 'temple-241038_640.jpg', 'temple-241038_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kolhapur is a significant city situated in the state of Maharashtra. The city has a rich history dating back to 300 years, and is located on the banks of the river Panchganga. The name Kolhapur is renowned all over India as well as abroad for its specialties like Kolhapuri Chappal, Kolhapuri food and Kolhapuri gur. As per a myth Kolhapur is named after the wish of a devil named Kolhasur, who was killed by Goddess Mahalakshmi. Kolhapur is famous as capital of Maratha film industry and has borne the glory and name as the place where the first feature film in India Raja Harischandra was conceptualized. The city is popular for the localized version of wrestling known as Kushti and also famous for art and education. Kolhapuri footwear, Kolhapuri jewels and Kolhapuri tobacco are known globally. These products are exported from Kolhapur. A modified version of necklace known as Kolhapuri Saaj is an excellent example of Kolhapur jewel products. Panhalgad hill station, Irwin Agricultural Museum, Mahalaxmi temple also called Dakshin Kashi and Bahubali Jain temple are few of the nearby Kolhapur attractions. Shopping is a superb experience in Kolhapur. You can get variety of products here at a very reasonable cost. Go through the Kolhapur travel guide and know more about the city.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kolhapur city is visited by a large number of people every year, comprising mainly of tourists and business travellers. The city offers adequate accommodation facilities with numerous hotels in the city, ranging from the business class ones to the budget ones. This is to ensure that travellers coming to Kolhapur find decent places to stay, which suits their budget as well as needs.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The Kolhapur Airport has regular flights from cities like Mumbai and Pune.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Kolhapur lies on the National Highway 4 which connects Mumbai and Bangalore. There are state run buses from Pune and Mumbai which leaves for Kolhapur one every half an hour and one hour respectively. There are private buses to Kolhapur as well.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Kolhapur Railway station is named after Chatrapati Shahu Maharaj and is well connected to major cities across India. It lies on the Pune Miraj Kolhapur section of the Central Railway.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Tranaport </strong>- Being a bustling city, state transport buses, rickshaws and taxis are readily available.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - KOLHAPUR - [FAMOUS FOR PANDHRA RASSA(NON VEG FOOD) IS A WHITE COLORED CHICKEN GRAVY WITH LOTS OF SPICES ; MISAL A SPICY GRAVY OF POTATOES, PEAS AND OTHER SPROUTS]&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - RAJBHAU, IN KOLHAPUR - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;BHELPURI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - THE OVEN, IN KOLHAPUR - (FAMOUS FOR PASTRIES, CAKES, PIZZAS, BURGERS, ROLLS AND CHOCOLATE SHAKES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - KHEMRAJ BAKERY, IN KOLHAPUR - (FAMOUS FOR BISCUITS, COOKIES AND BREAD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - PHADATARE, IN KOLHAPUR - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;SOL KADI (IS A TYPE OF CURRY)]<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n6 - FADATARE, IN KOLHAPUR - (FAMOUS FOR MISAL)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(640, 14, 31, 745, 'Maharashtra', 'INDIA', 'LATUR', 'yellow-845783_1280.jpg', 'yellow-845783_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">If there&rsquo;s one thing Latur shines most at, it&rsquo;s it affinity to educate tourists on the long legacy the place has to share. Latur, in South Eastern Maharashtra in India, part of the Marathwada region, boasts of historical locations and architecture, dating back to as far as the 7th century and very well preserved at that! Right from the Rashtrakuta kings in the 7th century to the rule of the Nizam under the British Raj in India in the early 1900s, Latur has had one action filled passed, which is evident in the various tourist places in and around the city. The city of Latur is situated wholly on the Balaghat plateau which is approximately 2000 feet above mean sea level, which makes for very pleasant weather in the winter months of the year. The Manjara River cuts right across the town of Latur and makes for a pleasant evening walk. Apart from the Manjara, Latur is also famous for several other rivers like Terna, Manyad, Lendi and Gharni. The Fort of Udgir is a prominent tourist place that has good scope for photography. Chakurconnects Latur to Nanded and houses a Shiva temple worth visiting during the travel. A good time to visit Latur is in the monsoon months if you&rsquo;re fond of the rains or are an avid photographer. The region receives plentiful rainfall and the rivers are a sight to be seen. Ever since the rule of the Nizam, Latur has been a strategic hub for trade in the Marathwada region. Even today, Latur is famous for its pulses like pigeon peas. If one wants to experiment with the growing concept of Agri tourism in Latur, it could make for quite an adventurous place given the extent of agricultural activities here.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The city of Latur offers good staying options. One can choose from big budget hotels ranging from luxurious star hotels to budget accommodations. The place also offers good lodges and guest houses.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Latur airport was initiated in the early 90s and ever since has been serving various charter and trade operators. Recently, an Indian Private airline began service to Latur from Nanded but that has been made seasonal for the moment. Latur airport has been revamped recently and offers the latest in Ground handling and Passenger services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Latur Railway station connects to various destinations in the North and Western regions of the State like Kolhapur, Pune, Mumbai and Nagpur. Additionally, Latur station connects to Hyderabad in Karnataka.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Driving down to Latur is pretty simple from various neighbouring towns via state highways 60, 77, 160 and 144. Furthermore, Latur is proximate to National Highway 9 that connects directly to Mumbai city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- State and private buses run on a regular basis from Latur to major cities of the state.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - VISHAL SWEET MART, IN LATUR - (FAMOUS FOR BARFI, LADOO, RASMALAI, KAJU BARFI AND SON PAPDI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - NEW TESTY BAKERY, IN LATUR - [FAMOUS FOR BREAD, PIZA BASE, CAKES AND KHARI(PUFF PASTARY)]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - YASHODA ICE AND COLD DRINKS, IN LATUR - (FAMOUS FOR MASALA COLD DRINK)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(641, 14, 31, 745, 'Maharashtra', 'INDIA', 'NAGPUR', 'oranges-1117628_640.jpg', 'oranges-1117628_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Popularly called the Orange City, Nagpur is an important city in Maharashtra. It is the state&rsquo;s 3rd largest city, following Mumbai and Pune. It is also known as the Tiger Capital of India. Found by the Gonds Dynasty, Nagpur was later taken over by the Bhonsles under the Maratha Empire. It was followed by the Britishers, who made Nagpur the capital of Central Province. Nagpur interestingly got its name from the Nag River that has a serpentine course, and Pur a common suffix associated with cities in Sanskrit and Hindi. The city&rsquo;s postal stamp still carries the image of a snake on it. This place is located on the Deccan Plateau at a height of 310 mts and covers an expanse of close to 10000 sq kms. Nagpur is revered for its green environment and comes second to Chandigarh in being the greenest place in India. It is the second capital of Maharashtra after Mumbai. Nawegaon Banhd, the Sitabuldi Fort and Pench National Park are a few major attractions in this place. Diksha Bhoomi is the iconic place where a thousand Dalits followed Dr. B. R. Ambedkar and converted to Buddhism. Nagpur is dotted with a host of lakes manmade and natural that are a must watch. Nagpur transforms into a bustling tourist place during the festivals of Navrathri, Dasshera, Ganesh Puja, Durga Puja, Moharram and many more. All these festivals are celebrated with much aplomb and warmth. Due to its location on the Deccan Plateau with no nearby major water body, Nagpur experiences extremes in temperature for both summers and winters. Monsoons are not an ideal time to visit this place, while the winters are the best for travelling.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Nagpur offers its visitors a wide variety of accommodation options to choose from. These include all the places to stay in the city, right from budget hotels, lodges and guesthouses to lavish five star hotels. As the booming city of the country, Nagpur has many hotel businesses set up by people and therefore one can easily find accommodations. Khindsi Lake is the best place for summer holidays. MTDC counters at rail stations and airport can also help with the accommodations.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Regular flight services ply to and fro Nagpur, 8.8 kms away from the main city is the nearest airport, Babasaheb Ambedkar International Airport, which serves regular domestic flights to her customers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Regular bus services ply to and fro Nagpur. Buses, in a range from affordable to slightly expensive rates, are available from places like Mumbai, Pune, Panjim, as the list goes on. Tourists can also take a shared taxi or cab for the same route.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Regular rail services ply to and fro Nagpur. Nagpur Junction railway station is the principal station that connects Indore to the rest of India via railways.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Buses, Autos and Taxis, one can prefer either. Buses are the most convenient mode of transport. Auto&#39;s and Taxis run on meters like other metro cities making it easy for the tourists to travel without being conned.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - NAGPUR - [FAMOUS FOR PITLA BHAKRI IS A DISH MADE FROM POWRERED DAL FORRMING A PASTY DISH ; EGGPLANT OR BHARLI VANGI IS A TRADITIONAL DISH MADE FROM STUFFED EGGPLANT WITH MIXTURE OF BOILED AND MINCED POTATOES, LOT OF SPICES, COCONUT AND PEANUTS ; ZUNKA BHAKA IS A TYPE OF PANCAKE IS MADE FROM MILLET FLOUR AND MIXTURE OF SPLIT GRAM ; KOSHAMBIR IS A TYPE OF SALAD MADE FROM RAW VEGETABLES AND FRUITS, FLAVOURED WITH BUTTER AND SPCES ; SANDAGE IS ANOTHER TRADITIONAL DISH COOKED WITH VEGETABLES AND SERVED WITH CHAPATTIS]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - SAMOSAWALA, IN NAGPUR - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA ARE SERVED WITH CHATNI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - PAKODEWALA,IN NAGPUR &nbsp;- (FAMOUS FOR PAKODAS AND SAMOSA WITH IMLI CHATNI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - PP&#39;S GRARAGE, IN NAGPUR - (FAMOUS FOR BUTTER CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - LA HORREE, IN NAGPUR - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;BUTTER NAAN WITH CHICKEN BHUNA MASALA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - SARDARJI KI RASOI, IN NAGPUR - (FAMOUS FOR TANDORI CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - BULLA&#39;S KITCHEN, IN NAGPUR - (FAMOUS FOR PANEER BUTTER MASALA, BUTTER CHICKEN AND GARLIC NAAN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - MINI PUNJAB, IN NAGPUR - (FAMOUS FOR BUTTER CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>9 - BABBU HOTEL, IN NAGPUR - (FAMOUS FOR TANDOORI CHICKEN AND MUTTON BIRYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>10 - HOTEL BARTANIA, IN NAGPUR - (FAMOUS FOR MUTTON CHOP, MURG MUSALLAM, HALEEM, MUTTON ROGANJOSH AND DUM BIRYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>11 - ANSAR HOTEL, IN NAGPUR - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;SAMOSA, PAKODA, MIRCHI BHAJIYA AND ARABI KHAJOOR)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>12 - GULGULA HOTEL, IN NAGPUR - (FAMOUS FOR GULGULA, RABDI, GULABJAMUN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>13 - HYDERABADI TANDOORI CHICKEN, IN NAGPUR - [FAMOUS FOR TANDOORI AND HARIYALI(CHICKEN)]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>14 - LUCKNOWI KEBAB CENTRE, IN NAGPUR - (FAMOUS FOR BEEF KORMA, CHICKEN, MURGH MALAI AND PINEAPPALE CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>15 - HAFEEZ BAKERY, IN NAGPUR - (FAMOUS FOR ROTT, SHEERMALL, COOKIES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>16 - HOTEL TANVEER, IN NAGPUR - (FAMOUS FOR BIRYANI AND TANDOORI CHICKEN AND KEBABS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>17 - ML CANTEEN, IN NAGPUR - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKE/MUTTON DUM BIRYANI AND MUTTON SUKKA)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(643, 14, 31, 745, 'Maharashtra', 'INDIA', 'NANDURBAR', 'drawing-2058117_640.jpg', 'drawing-2058117_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Nandurbar is the district headquarters in the state of Maharashtra which is bounded to the south and southeast by Dhule district, to the west and north is the state of Gujarat, to the north and northeast is the state of Madhya Pradesh. The northern boundary of the district is defined by the great Narmada River. Nandurbar got its name from a Gavali king, Nandaraja. The Administration of Nandurbar District comprises six taluks. These taluks are Akkalkuwa, Akrani Mahal, Taloda, Shahada, Nandurbar and Navapur. Although the region consists of the tribal belt of Maharashtra state but has several places of tourist importance. Prakasha, one of the famous religious places, also known as Dakshin Kashi, is in Shahada Tehsil. Ahirani, Bhili language, Pardhi, Marathi language, Hindi language and Gujari are the main languages spoken in Nandurbar district. Agriculture is the main source of economy of the district. The place also offers many temples and prominent monuments of historical importance. The temples within the region attract thousands of people who visit on the occasion of various festivals. A predominantly tribal pocket, which has been socially and politically alert, Nandurbar district, has become internationally known for the first project of manufacturing particle boards from sugarcane biogases in the world.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Nandurbar has handful of hotels, located in the close vicinity of the major tourist spots. The budget hotels in provide clean and spacious accommodation with basic amenities that are required for a pleasant and comfortable stay.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The closest major airport is the Chhatrapati Shivaji airport at Mumbai. One can even avail the domestic airport at Gondur or Aurangabad too.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Nandurbar Railway Station is on the railway line that connects Udhna with Jalgaon. It is managed by the Western Railways. Dondaicha Railway Station is the main station to the east of Nandurbar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- MSRTC Govt. and Private bus services ply from Nandurbar to major cities in and around Maharashtra.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Nandurbar is on the Maharashtra State Highway 1 which connects to Dhule. Taxis and buses run on a regular basis.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - NANDURBAR - [FAMOUS FOR JHUNKA IS A DISH PREPARED FROM GRAM FLOUR(BESAN) MIX WITH WATER TO FORM A STIFF PASTE ; SOLKADHI IS A SOUP IS PREPARED WITH KOKAM AND COCONUT MILK]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '');
