(644, 14, 31, 745, 'Maharashtra', 'INDIA', 'NASHIK', 'butterfly-166785_640.jpg', 'butterfly-166785_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The city of Nashik is situated in Maharashtra and is known as the Wine Capital of India, given the quantity of grapes it produces. It is around 180 kms away from Mumbai and close to 200 kms from Pune. The &lsquo;Napa Valley&rsquo; lies on the Western Ghats. Nashik was formerly the capital of the Satvahana Dynasty. During the 16th Century, the city came under the Mughal rule and was called Gulshanabad. From them it went over to the Peshwas, who finally lost the place to the Britishers in the 19th Century. Famous freedom fighters like Veer Savarkar are from Nashik. It is suggested that the exile of 14 years that Lord Ram was banished to was spent near Nashik, at a place called Tapovan. At this very place, Lord Laksham cut off Shurpanakha&rsquo;s nose, and hence this place came to be called Nasik, which translates to a Nose. Kalidas, Valmiki have spoken of Nashik in their works. The renowned philosopher of 150 BC, Plotemy, too mentioned Nashik. Nashik is presently Maharashtra&rsquo;s fastest growing city. Infrastructure, education, industrial, and a numerous other aspects Nashik has developed tremendously in each of these spheres. Nashik is famous for its production of grapes. The Sula Vineyard is a must visit for keen wine tasters. The delectable chivda from here should not be missed. Given its location, the climate of Nashik is tropical, giving rise to extreme temperatures. As a result the hot summers are generally avoided for travelling, while the cool winters make for a perfect get away time. The monsoon season is also a beautiful time to be spent in this city, although this only poses as a good option for rain lovers.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">As a pilgrimage holy city, Nashik offers visitors a good range of hotels and accommodations from the upper end to small local dharmashalas (guest houses). These hotels range from luxurious five star and four star hotels to medium priced three star hotels, economy hotels and even cheap budget hotels. Favoured for providing professional services amid homely comfort, these hotels serve as the perfect retreats to unwind and relax amid a calm and peaceful setting.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The Mumbai Chattrapti Shivaji International Airport is the closest international as well as domestic airport to Nashik, at about a distance of 185 kms. The International Airport is, in turn, linked to all major airports in India and abroad.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Nashik is very well connected to all the major towns and cities within the state of Maharahstra via trains.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - The NH 3 National Highway connects Nashik to Mumbai via the Thane Kasar Igatpuri path. Nashik is also connected to Pune with NH 50.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - There are several private luxury video coaches and state buses available between Nashik and cities like Pune, Shirdi, Aurangabad and Mumbai. Maharashtra State Transport buses connect Nashik to distant places of Maharashtra.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - NASHIK - [FAMOUS FOR MAKAI CHIVDA IS A SNACK MADE FROM CORN OR MAIZE ; AMTI IS ATYPE OF DAL &nbsp;IS PREPARED WITH YELLOW LENTILS AND SPICED WITH CHILLIES, GARAM MASALA AND CURRY LEAVES ; BATATA VADA IS A FRIED SNACK &nbsp;; GULACHI POLI (INDIAN BREAD) IS ASWEET DISH &nbsp;MADE FROM WHEAT FLOUR AND FILLED WITH JAGGERY AND PEANUTS]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - CAMPUS CHOICE, IN NASHIK - (FAMOUS FOR PANEER PATTIES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - SAI CHINESE, IN NASHIK - (FAMOUS FOR MANCHURIAN NOODLES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - VIJU, IN NASHIK - [FAMOUS FOR DABELI(IS A SNACK)]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - SAI LEELA, IN NASHIK - (FAMOUS FOR LONI SPONGE DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - YUMMY TUMMY, IN NASHIK - (FAMOUS FOR SANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - CANADA CORNER, IN NASHIK - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN SHWARMA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>8 - THE DOODLE CAFE, IN NASHIK - (FAMOUS FOR PATTIES BURGERS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>9 - MODERN CAFE, IN NASHIK - (FAMOUS FOR THALIPEETH, POHE AND MISAL)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>10 - AL ARABIAN EXPRESS, IN NASHIK - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;KEBAB)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n11 - THUNDER POINT, IN NASHIK - (FAMOUS FOR VARITIES OF JUICES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>12 - AGRAWAL BROS K MITHAIWALA, IN NASHIK - (FAMOUS FOR SNACKS SWEETS, COLD DRINKS, ICE CREAM AND SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>13 - TULSA SNACKS - (FAMOUS FOR POHE, UPAMA AND SABUDANA KHICHADI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>14 - SAYANTARA, IN NASHIK - (FAMOUS FOR SABUDANA VADA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>15 - NANDANS, IN NASHIK - (FAMOUS FOR PANI PURI AND OTHER CHAAT)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>16 - SHOUKIN, IN NASHIK - (FAMOUS FOR BHEL PURI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>17 - JALARAM SWEETS, IN NASHIK - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>18 - BUDHA HALWAI, IN NASHIK - (FAMOUS FOR CHIVADA, SAMOSA AND POTATO JALEBI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>19 - MAHARASHTRA BHAANDAAR, IN NASHIK - (FAMOUS FOR LADDUS, CHIVDA, KARANJI, SHEV, CHAKLI AND FARSAAN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>20 - BHAGVATIS, IN NASHIK - (FAMOUS FOR CHAAT ITEM)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>21 - MAMA&#39;S PAV BHAAJI, IN NASHIK - (FAMOUS FOR PAV BHAAJI AND ALL KINS OF CHAAT ITEMS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>22 - ROLLS CLUB, IN NASHIK - (FAMOUS FOR ROLLS AND KEEMA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>23 - BLISS JUICE BAR, IN NASHIK - (FAMOUS FOR COFFEE, TEA, MILKSHAKES, SANDWICHES, WRAPS, PIZZA AND BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>24 - BAGGA SWEETS, IN NASHIK - [FAMOUS FOR BUTTERMILK(LASSI)]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(645, 14, 31, 745, 'Maharashtra', 'INDIA', 'OSMANABAD', 'india-1006240_640.jpg', 'india-1006240_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Osmanabad lies in the southern part of Maharashtra State. It is a district headquarters with most of the area being rocky while the remaining part is plain. The region is surrounded by a small mountain called Balaghat. Bhoom, Washi, Kalamb, Osmanabad &amp; Tuljapur Tehsil lie in the range of this Balaghat Mountain. Osmanabad derives its name from the king of Hyderabad State Nizam Osman Ali. Osmanabad was formerly known as Dharashiv, is situated in the Marathwada region of Maharashtra. The city is known as the Gateway to Marathwada, is also an important religious destination for Hindus, Jain and Buddhists people. It is known all over India due to Goddess Tulja Bhavani. The town is the district headquarters of Osmanabad region and is famous for the growth of Jowar, sunflower, sugarcane and tur crops. &nbsp;With an area of 7550 sq kms, Osmanabad has a number of places that tourist can visit, both of religious significance as well as leisurely interest. For the pilgrims visiting the temples of Shri Tulja Bhavani Temple and the Saint Goroba Kaka Temple are of prime importance. Among other attractions, the region also offers the Dharashiv Caves, the Naldurg Fort and the Paranda Fort. Marathi is the official language.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Osmanabad offers good hotels ranging from luxurious star hotels to budget hotels, dharamshalas and lodges. The hotels are homely and laced with the modern amenities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport is at Solapur about 70 kms which is linked to Mumbai by air. Pune is another airport nearby.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Osmanabad is an important Railway Station on Kurduwadi Latur Section of Central Railway. Initially there was no railway route to Osmanabad. The nearest railway station was Yedshi about 22 kms on Barshi Kurduwadi narrow gauge route of Central Railway.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Regularly government MSRTC and private buses ply from Osmanabad to major cities within the state.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - State highways and metallic roads from the district headquarters at Osmanabad link all 8 sub districts and major towns within Maharashtra and neighbouring states. A national highway passes through the district from Solapur, connecting Karnataka to Andhra Pradesh.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - PRESTIGE RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT S.R.T.COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR GULAB JAMUN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - JATRA HEALTH RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT LAKSHMI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR SHEVBHAAJI CURRY)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - LAZZIS, LOCATED AT INDIRA COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN BIRYANI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - HOTEL NANDANWAN, LOCATED IN OSMANABAD - (FAMOUS FOR PARATHA DHAI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - ABHINAV SWEETS KUNTHALGIRI, LOCATED IN OSMANABAD- (FAMOUS FOR PEDHA)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(646, 14, 31, 745, 'Maharashtra', 'INDIA', 'PALGHAR', 'landscape-629809_6402.jpg', 'landscape-629809_6403.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Located in the state of Maharashtra in Thane district, Palghar is a large town and is the heart of various Industrial Townships having numerous small scale industries such as engineering, pharmaceutical, plastics and textile and notebook industries. Palghar travel guide is full of historical and pilgrim references. The vicinity of the town is pollution free and very calm and serene dotted with lush green vegetation. Palghar is bounded by several villages such as Kelva, Satpati, Shirgaon, Tarapur, Boisar and Umroli. Satpati is one of the most renowned and the largest fishing centres of Maharashtra called as is situated just 8 kms from Palghar. Rice is the main cash crop and is cultivated here in large quantity. Palghar is considered as an industrial township and there are quite a few small scale industries located here. There are many beautiful places to see in and around Palghar which draw in regular tourists. The Kelva dam with its beautiful garden constructed many years back is not only a source of irrigation, but also a nice place to visit. The Kelva Fort and Shirgoan Fort located nearby are popular tourist sites along with the many beautiful beaches like Kelva Beach, Mahim Beach and Satpati Beach. There are also a number of picturesque lakes and some famous Hindu temples like the Ram Mandir and the Sheetala Devi Mandir which add to the beauty of the town.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Palghar has a lot for deluxe and medium to budget accommodation options. Some of the deluxe accommodation options include Kelva Beach Resort, Anand Residency, Shantashil Resort and Aryan Farm. Other medium and budget accommodations include Sai Residency Hotel, Sheetal Chhaya, Laxmi Guest House and Pritam Resort Hotel.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest International Airport is Chhatrapati Shivaji International Airport, Mumbai, roughly two hour drive from Palghar. It is well connected to a spectrum of cities in the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Palghar has its own Railway Station named as Palghar Railway Station which is connected to the major cities of Maharashtra. It is linked with the cities like New Delhi, Bangalore, Mysore, Jamnagar, Chennai, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - There are no bus routes from other major cities to Palghar. Nearest bus stand is Vasai about 35 kms away from Palghar.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - PALGHAR - [FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN BUJING (FRIED POHA, FRIED POTATOES,CHICKEN WITH LOTS OF INGREDIENTS IN IT)]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - SHREE DATTA SNACKS, IN PALGHAR - (FAMOUS FOR MISAL PAV, WADA PAV, KOTHIMBIR WADI AND TEA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - ANAM, IN PALGHAR - (FAMOUS FOR MISAL PAV, MASALA DOSA, IDLI, AND MEDU WADA SAMBHAR)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - BHOLENATH, IN PALGHAR - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORI, SAMOSA AND VADA PAV)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - JALARAM SNACKS BAR, IN PALGHAR - (FAMOUS FOR VADA PAV AND PAV BHAJJI)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(647, 14, 31, 745, 'Maharashtra', 'INDIA', 'PARBHANI', 'sunset-2028653_6402.jpg', 'sunset-2028653_6403.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Parbhani was named after Goddess Prabhavati the Goddess with Great Aura. The region didn&rsquo;t do well for itself under the Sultans, Mughals and Nizams of the Muslim Dynasty. For around 650 years, Parbhani stayed a stagnated village. However, once it was merged with Maharashtra in 1960, the place started to prosper. Parbhani is most famous for being the holy site of Sai Baba&rsquo;s a reincarnation of Dattatraya birth at a place called Pathri, about 45 kms away. The Jabareshwar Beleshwar Mahadev, the Mota Maruthi and the Pardeshwara are few of the many religious shrines that can be found here. The Jain Temple of Jintur is another fantastic holy spot 40 kms away. A village nearby that goes by the name Mudgal is said to be the only place where Lord Vishnu and Lord Shiva are worshipped together. The Narsimha Temple is another famous temple here. The temple of Shri Keshavraj Babasaheb deserves special mention, as he was Shri Sai Baba&rsquo;s Guruji. This temple is located at Selu, about 45 kilometres away from Parbhani. Earlier known as Parbhavatinagar, Parbhani is a district located in the state of Maharashtra. It figures as one amongst the eight districts of the Marathwada region. It is set at an altitude of 357 mts above sea level and is flanked by the Balaghat Hills and the Ajanta Hills on either side. Parbhani has religious significance in Hindu Mythology. It is a birthplace of saints, Sai Baba being one of the most celebrated and revered ones. There are numerous temples situated in the nearby vicinity.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">The city of Parbhani is equipped with decent staying options which include luxurious lodges, economy to budget hotels and guesthouses. MTDC provides 3 double bedded rooms with restaurant facilities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air </strong>- The Nanded Domestic Airport is the closest domestic airport to Parbhani about 60 kms away. The flights operating from this airport is fairly regular about four days a week.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Train </strong>- Parbhani is well accessible by rail from many major cities and towns within and outside the state of Maharashtra. There are daily, regular trains that connect Parbhani to cities like Mumbai, Pune, Hyderabad, Delhi and Nashik.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Bus</strong> - There are several Private Tour Operators and state transport buses that ply between Parbhani and various other cities in Maharashtra like Mumbai and Pune. Private Buses generally pose as a better alternative to state owned transport services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Road</strong> - State highways and roads from the district headquarters at Parbhani connect all nine sub districts and major towns.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(648, 14, 31, 745, 'Maharashtra', 'INDIA', 'RAIGAD', 'panchgani-1650030_6404.jpg', 'panchgani-1650030_6405.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Raigad is located in south western side of Maharashtra State. The Situated on western coast of India and on the shore of Arabian Sea, Raigad is on a west facing spur of the Western Ghats of Sahyadri range. The district is bounded by Mumbai Harbour to the northwest, Thane district to the north, Pune district to the east, Ratnagiri district to the south, and the Arabian Sea to the west. It&rsquo;s believed that Raigad was named after the Rairi hill, on which the Raigad fort was constructed and fortified by Shivaji and his engineers, notably Abaji Sondev, the then governor of Kalyan. Situated in western coastal stretch of Maharashtra Konkan region is the mountainous terrain of Raigad, famed for its breathtaking natural beauty as evident from its canyons, deep gorges and lush vegetation. The beauty of the place is further enhanced by the crisscrossing rivers of Gandhar and Kal that rushes down through the beautiful valley. Raigad is a beautiful hill fort immensely important in the history of Maharashtra. Raigad fills every mind with a sense of awe and respect towards its grandeur and glorious past. Gifted with a mountainous terrain and nestled in the Sahyadri mountain range this lovely place offers breathtaking views of natural splendour. Raigad is distinguished from the nearby mountains by lovely and profound canyons. A verdant valley with rivers flowing beneath makes the surroundings scenic and tranquil. Adorned with a hilly terrain and natural foliage, Raigad&#39;s awesome beauty gains a prominent place in the tourism sector. It&#39;s serene, calm topography is certainly a solace to those who are coming from a busy city life.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Raigad has several hotels, resorts and MTDC guest houses which are available at various rates. There are many five star hotels, budget hotels as well as lodges. Raigad has many deluxe to medium budget accommodation options to suit needs of all kinds of travel budgets.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Nearest airport to Raigad is the Mumbai Airport, which is at a distance of 140 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- The Sion Panvel Expressway connects Mumbai and Raigad district. State transport is available from Mumbai, Pune, Kolhapur and Mahableshwar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Vis Dasgaon Railway station is the closest station to Raigad and is connected by Mumbai Pune long distance trains.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - State transport buses connect all the cities in the Raigad district. There are regular buses that go towards Raigad Fort. Rickshaws are also available here.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SHREE DATTA SNACKS, IN RAIGAD - (FAMOUS FOR THALIPEETH, KOTHIMBIR WADI, KANDEPOHE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - HAPPY, IN RAIGAD - (FAMOUS FOR BURGERS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(649, 14, 31, 745, 'Maharashtra', 'INDIA', 'RATNAGIRI', 'AA63.jpg', 'AA64.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\nSituated in the south western region of the state of Maharashtra, Ratnagiri is a small yet beautiful port city on the coast of the Arabian Sea. After Shivaji Maharaj&rsquo;s rule in this part of India, Ratnagiri was under the Satar Kings&rsquo; territory in and around 1731 before the British took over the place in 1818. Mythological stories claim that post their 12 year exile, the Pandavas, of the Mahabharata fame, spent quite some time in Ratnagiri. The King who ruled the place back then had supported their fight against the Kauravas by personally participating in the battle of Mahabharata. Situated in pretty surroundings, Ratnagiri is blessed with hills, sea shores, creeks, beautiful rivers, hot water springs, forests and waterfalls and offers a rejuvenating experience to travelers. Ratnagiri is a travellers dream come true destination with its majestic Sahyadri range and Arabian sea with virginal white beaches, cascading waterfalls, hot water springs palm groves, majestic monuments and the most famous, Alphonso mangoes. Ratnagiri has some of the magnificent forts built during the Shivaji period. Ratnagiri is also famous as the birthplace of Lokmanya Bal Gangadhar Tilak who was one third of the famous trio of &quot;Lal Bal Pal&quot;. One of the gems in Konkan region, Ratnagiri is now a big district comprising of several touristy small villages and towns and it forms for a brilliant weekend getaway from the cities of Maharashtra including Mumbai.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Hotels with a beach view are quite popular among tourists. Tourists will find plenty of mid range and luxury hotels near the beaches. One would also find budget hotels in the city. Since the city is a hotspot among tourists, it is advisable to book rooms beforehand, especially on weekends.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Ratnagiri is very conveniently located in terms of air travel. It has its own Domestic Airport, about 12 kms away from the heart of the district. It is well connected by daily flights to Mumbai and Delhi and all other major towns and cities across Maharashtra.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The stations of Ratnagiri lie on the Konkan Railway. It is well linked to almost all cities and towns throughout in India via regular trains.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - The NH 17 highway passes through this district. The Ratnagiri Nagpur National Highway, named NH 204, links Ratnagiri to the eastern cities and towns of India like Solapur, Nanded, and of course, Nagpur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Regular bus services are available from many cities in Maharashtra to Ratnagiri. State owned and private buses ply from Ratnagiri to many cities in and around. Evening trips of tourist luxury buses are available from Mumbai to Ratnagiri.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Travelling within Ratnagiri is not a problem as there are numerous local buses, auto rickshaws and taxis.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - RATNAGIRI - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;THALIPEETH(IS A TYPE OF PANCAKE) MADE FROM ROASTED TAPIOCA, RAJGARA, CORIANDER SEEDS, CUMIN SEEDS, WHEAT AND RICE ; GHAVAN IS A DOSA MADE WITH RICE FLOUR AND SERVED WITH CHUTNEY ; ZUNKA BHAKRI IS A DISH MADE WITH BESAN, ONIONS AND SPICES ; MANIK PAINJAN IS A TRADITIONAL DISH MADE WITH CHANNA DAL WHEAT FLOUR AND GRAM FLOUR DURING SPECIAL OCCASIONS ; DHONDUS IS AMALWANI CUCUMBER CAKE MADE WITH SEMOLINA, COCONUT AND JAGGERY ; THE NARALI BHAT IS A DISH MADE WITH RICE, COCONUT AND JAGGERY ; KONKANI IS A NON VEGETARIAN DISH MADE OF CHICKEN AND RICE &nbsp;; KOKAM SHARBAT IS A SWEET DRINK PREPARED BY SOAKING THE KOKUM IN HOT WATER, WITH ROASTED CUMIN SEED POWDER, BLACK PEPPER AND SUGAR</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(650, 14, 31, 745, 'Maharashtra', 'INDIA', 'SINDHUDURG', 'sunset-1198134_640.jpg', 'sunset-1198134_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The name Sindhudurg is a combination of words Sindhu, which means the sea, and Durg, which translates to a fort. It was built by the great Maratha warrior King, Chattrapati Shivaji. He chose this rocky island location to suit his strategic purpose of countering foreign forces, and to keep the Siddis of Murud-Janjira in check. The beauty of this fort is that, it is built in such a fashion, that it could not be easily seen by the enemies that came from the Arabian Sea. The major attractions here are the beaches, not to mention, the numerous forts. In earlier days, built around the 17th Century, Sindhudurg was Maharashtra&rsquo;s most important sea forts. The Sindhudurg Fort has a zigzag rampart with 42 bastions. The building material itself comprises close to 73,000 kg of iron. At a time when travelling by sea was banned by holy Hindu scriptures, this massive construction represents the revolutionary mindset of the Maratha King. Till date, tourists from all over the world visit the Padmagarh fort to witness this Maratha glory. Sindhudurg is also home to one of India&rsquo;s oldest Sai Baba Temples. Sindhudurg is located in the Konkan area of Maharashtra. This fortress is situated in an islet off the shore of Malvan, and was carved out of the Ratnagiri district. Endowed with majestic mountains, exotic seashore, and glorious scenery, this place is popular for Alphonso Mangoes, cashews, jamuns, etc. On a clear day, one can see the clear sea bed up to a depth of almost 20 feet. Indian and foreign tourists love to explore the region and go scuba diving and snorkelling to help themselves with a visual treat of exotic coral reefs on the outskirts of the island. This region is extremely renowned for its unique Malvani Cuisine. The region of Sindhudurg experiences a humid climate. Summers are usually hot and travellers are advised to rather travel during the winter season, more specifically in December and January, when the weather is much cooler and pleasant.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Sindhudurg has several hotels, resorts and MTDC guest houses which are available at various rates. There are many five star hotels, budget hotels as well as lodges.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport is the Dabolim Airport in Goa about 120 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - Konkan Railway line passes through this district. It has good rail links with Goa and Bombay.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Bus</strong> - There are state government (MSRTC) buses running from Mumbai, Pune, Ratnagiri, Sangli, Kolhapur and Panaji to Sindhudurg.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road </strong>- NH 17 runs throughout the length of the whole of the district. Well connected by roads to major cities around. Like its counterpart on rail, this route is also very scenic.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - SINDHUDURG - [FAMOUS FOR MALVANI LADDOOS MADE FROM GRAM FLOUR AND JAGGERY ; SOLKADHI IS ATYPE OF CURRY MADE WITH KOKKUM FRUIT, COCONUT CHILLIES AND SPICES]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - VIJAYA BAKERY, IN SINDHUDURG - [FAMOUS FOR SOFT CAKE, BERRY BISCUITS, KHARI(PUFF PASTRY BIOSCUIT)]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(651, 14, 31, 745, 'Maharashtra', 'INDIA', 'SOLAPUR', 'tree-2079659_640.jpg', 'tree-2079659_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\nOne of the most prominent cities in the state of Maharashtra, Solapur district covers an area of about 14850 sq kms and is surrounded by districts like Osmanabad and Ahmednagar to the north, Satara and Pune to the west, Bijapur and Sangli in the south and Gulbarga District in the east. Solapur was historically dominated by several dynasties like the Chalukyas, the Yadavas, the Andhrabhratyas, the Rashtrkutas and the Bahamanis. The Solapur district was taken over from the Bahamani kingdom by the Bijapur Kings. It was later passed over to the Maratha rulers. The fall of Peshwa in 1818 saw the British Government occupy Solapur and it was made a sub division of the Ahmednagar district then. As recent as 1960 saw Solapur get its own tag of a district of the Maharashtra state. Situated on the bank of the River Sina, Solapur is recognized as a premier Jain religious centre in Maharashtra. Historians believe that the district got its name from Sola Pur which means Sixteen Villages in Hindi. Solapur is extremely popular for Pandharpur the Dakshin Kashi of India. Pandharpur is revered as the city of Lord Vitthoba and a prime example of a fine religious centre in the entire country. The festivals of Kartiki and Ashadhi Ekadashi see pilgrims to the tune of four to five lakhs coming here. Akkalkot is a very significant pilgrim centre nearby Solapur. It is dedicated to Shri Swami Samarth Maharaj an incarnate of Lord Dattatreya. The Vatavrikhsa Temple found here is a must visit, and so is the Swami&rsquo;s Math. Tuljapur is home to the temple of Goddess Tulja Bhawani and is an added destination to the list of pilgrim centres found here. The Motibaug Tank is a wonderful site for bird watching. Tonnes of migratory birds flock here during the winter season. The Revanisiddheshwar Temple lies nearby this tank. Also present in the proximity is Nannaj the Great Indian Bustard Sanctuary, yet another place for wildlife enthusiasts. Solapur is not only a great city to visit, but also a fantastic place to live and work. It is a great place where the diverse cultures of Marathi, Kannada and Telugu seamlessly amalgamate.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">As numerous visitors including pilgrims and tourists reach Solapur every year, the city homes several top quality hotels that provide comfortable accommodation to the people. From five star hotels to budget hotels, these lodging facilities are suitable for people of all classes. Sholapur has good hotels ranging from luxurious 5 star hotels to budget hotels.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The Solapur Airport is the best option for air travel if travellers plan to fly in to Solapur. It is situated towards the south of the city. However, tourists from abroad can settle for the Chattrapati Shivaji Airport, an international airport in Mumbai that has connecting flights to Solapur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Solapur is easily accessible by rail thanks to the Solapur Railway station. This station is connected to all the cities and towns within and outside Maharashtra with the help of local and out station trains.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - The national highways 9, 13 and 211 pass through Solapur city. Solapur is located on Pune Hyderabad NH 9, approximately 275 kms away from Pune. It is also well connected by road.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - State transports ply buses from major cities of the state like Mumbai, Aurangabad and Pune to Solapur. Regularly government and private buses ply from Pune.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SOLAPUR - [FAMOUS FOR LALPSHI IS MADE WITH BROKEN WHEAT ; SHENGADANA CHATANI(GROUNDNUT CHUTNEY)IS AMIXTURE OF GROUNDNUT, CHILLI POWDER AND GARLIC]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - SUPRAJA, IN SOLAPUR&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;- (FAMOUS FOR PAV BHAJI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - CAFE MIDDLE EAST, IN SOLAPUR - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN ROLL AND CHICKEN WINGS)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(652, 14, 31, 745, 'Maharashtra', 'INDIA', 'WARDHA', 'flower-1753442_1920.jpg', 'flower-1753442_19201.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Wardha holds a prolific place in history of being the land that was ruled by several great kingdoms consisting of the Chalukyas, the Mauryas, the Rajputs and the Satavahanas. Wardha was first under the captivation of the Bahamani Kingdom back in 1351. It later came under the Imad Shahi Rulers in 1518 when the Bahamani dynasty disintegrated. Post the invasion of the Mughal Dynasties, the region of Wardha finally came under the British Rule. Wardha played an extremely significant role in India&rsquo;s Freedom chapter by serving as the site of Gandhiji&rsquo;s ashram. Founded in 1866, the district of Wardha is located in the state of Maharashtra. The city within the district, that shares the same name, got its name from the Wardha River that flows through the place. The place is sprawled over a massive area of 6310 sq kms. Wardha presently serves as a prominent cotton trade centre and was historically significant in the Gandhian Era. Wardha is famous for its numerous temples like the Gitai Mandir, the Laxmi Narayan Mandir, the Mahakali Mandir and the Kelzer Temple. The weather at Wardha is optimal at almost all times. The summers can get a little hot to handle, however the mild winters with the cool breezes make up for it.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Wardha city offers decent staying options for visitors. One can choose from, budget to luxury hotels, guesthouses and lodges with basic amenities at affordable prices.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The Dr. Babasaheb Ambedkar Airport at Nagpur is the closest International Airport to Wardha, about 74 kms away.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Wardha serves as a prominent and important railway station on the Konkan Line. It is well linked by several trains to major cities like Pune, Nagpur and Mumbai.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - There are several state owned and private tour uses available that link Wardha by road to cities like Nagpur, Pune and Mumbai.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - WARDHA - [FAMOUS FOR GHADICHI POLI IS A TYPE OF BREAD MADE OF WHEAT ; BHAKRI IS ATYPE OF BREAD MADE FROM MILLETS ; PURAN POLI IS A SWEET FLATBREADMADE FROM WHEAT, SUGAR AND YELLOW GRAM</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(653, 14, 31, 745, 'Maharashtra', 'INDIA', 'WASHIM', 'crow-391145_640.jpg', 'crow-391145_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Washim district is located in the Vidarbha Region of Maharashtra state. The entire district occupies an area of about 5150 sq kms which is surrounded by Akola, Amravati, Buldhana, Yavatmal and Parbhani. The Rivers Penganag and Aran pass through this district. It&#39;s believed that Washim gets its name from Basim, an Arabic name that means the one that smile. The name originated in Saudi Arabia in 436 AD when Basim R. Iqbal ruled the Jamar clan. Washim is a city and a municipal council in Washim district in the Indian state of Maharashtra. Washim is the head quarter of the newly formed Washim district. The place is famous as a pilgrimage centre where devotees believe that Tirupathi&#39;s Lord Balaji comes here for resting after the crop harvest. The Pohara Devi temple is known as Kashi of the Banjara community. In ancient times, it was the capital of King Wakatak, also known as Vatsagulma. During British regime, Washim acquired the status of a district due to its strategic location. Hemadpanthi temples and numerous ponds have made the district famous. Washim is known to have had 108 Tirthas, holy places or sacred springs, associated with different gods and sages. The Padma Thirtha is one of the chief Tirthas erected by Lord Vishnu. The district is filled with several temples and ponds and serves as a good weekend getaway.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Washim city is equipped with decent accommodation facilities, which vary from luxurious lodges and hotels. There are some reasonable accommodation options too at the numerous guesthouses and tourist lodges in the city. MTDC provides 3 double bedded rooms with restaurant facilities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport is at Nanded which is 106 kms from Washim. Alternatively, one can also opt for the airport at Aurangabad which is at a distance of 200 kms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Washim has its own railway station. It is on the Khandwa Purna, Narrow gauge railway line. Karanja is another city close by which has another railway junction.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Govt. and private buses ply on a regular basis to Washim from different major cities of Maharashtra.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Washim is connected by State Highways to all the important cities of Maharashtra.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - NEW MALWA PUNJABI DHABA, LOCATED AT NAGPUR-AURANGABAD-MUMBAI HIGHWAY, GHIVHA PATA VILLAGE - (FAMOUS FOR CHANA KE DAL)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - CAFE NSB, LOCATED AT MH SH 183 - (FAMOUS FOR SANDWICH, BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - BREWERS, LOCATED AT CHARKHA COMPLEX, AKOLA NAKA - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA, COFFEE AND BURGERS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(654, 14, 31, 745, 'Maharashtra', 'INDIA', 'YAVATMAL', 'wild-jack-346410_640.jpg', 'wild-jack-346410_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Yavatmal is located in the region of Vidarbha, in the east central part of the Maharashtra state. The district is situated in the Wardha Penganga Wainganga plain bounded by Amravati district in the north, Wardha district in the northeast, Chandrapur district in the east, Washim district in the west and the Hingoli district in the Southeast. Yavatmal derives its name from Yavat meaning mountain and Mal meaning row. Its believed that originally the town was known as Yotmaad and if one separates this term into two, we get Yot which means proximate land and Maad means tall trees, initially this town was called Yeotmal by British, Gradually the word Yeotmal undergone some changes and a new word Yavatmal came into existence. Yavatmal is located in the north eastern part of Maharashtra State, which is also a district administrative centre. The surrounding region of Yavatmal presents a contrast between the river valleys in the north and the south and the drier plateau in the centre. The region, as a whole, awaits development. Yavatmal is one of the smallest districts in the state in respect of the population, and fairly on the high side in respect of the area. The chief rivers of the district are Wardha and Penganga, both of which flow respectively along of the northern and southern boundaries of the district. The whole district of Yavatmal is occupied by small east west Range of Ajanta Mountains. Yavatmal district is one of the major cotton growing districts in the state. There are a number of tourist destinations in the district. Fairs are also held in various parts of the district throughout the year.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The city of Yavatmal is well equipped with good staying options which include luxurious hotels to economy and deluxe hotels, lodges and budget accommodations. MTDC also provides a few guest houses and dormitory.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The Dr. Babasaheb Ambedkar International Airport at Nagpur is the nearest Airport to Yavatmal, about 140 kms away. The Nagpur Airport is well linked by regular, daily flights to all the major towns and cities within the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The Yavatmal station in the city is well connected to the major cities within the state of Maharashtra like Pune, Mumbai, Nagpur and Ahmednagar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Yavatmal is very easily accessible by road. One can opt for the National Highway 7, from Nagpur or Hyderabad. The State Highway from Amravati to Chandrapur also passes through Yavatmal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - There are several state transport buses and private tour operators that facilitate the commuting between various towns and cities within Maharashtra and Yavatmal. The fare depends on the type of bus.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - GOLI VADAPAV, LOCATED AT PANGARI - (FAMOUS FOR PALAK MAKAI AND VADA PAV)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - BURGER STREET, LOCATED AT PESHWE PLOT, NEAR AKRUTI PLAZA - (FAMOUS FOR HOT DOGS AND MASALA DRINKS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - CAFE BEANS, LOCATED AT CIVIL LINES, CHURCH ROAD, PANGARI - (FAMOUS FOR A LATTE IS A COFFEE DRINK MADE FROM ESPRESSO AND MILK)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - GAGAN SHARMA SHEGAON, LOCATED AT MSH 3, VAIDYA NAGAR, BHARTI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - HOTEL GUPTA, LOCATED AT ARUNODAYA SOCIETY - (FAMOUS FOR DAHI ALOO WADA &nbsp;AND SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - CHAI KI TAPRI, LOCATED AT SHRE KRISHNA NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR FRUIT JUCIE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - KAKA RESTAURANT, LOCATED IN YAVATMAL - (FAMOUS FOR BUTTER CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>8 - SHREE BHOLENATH, LOCATED AT ARUNODAYA SOCIETY, VYANKATESHWAR NAGAR, GODHANI ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR PANIPURI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n9 - CHETAN DHORAJIWALA SWEET MART, LOCATED AT NEAR PUNJAB NATIONAL BANK, NEHRU CHOWK - (FAMOUS FOR PYAZ KI KACHORI)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(655, 14, 31, 745, 'Maharashtra', 'INDIA', 'PRABHANI', 'yellow-footed-green-pigeon-381356_640.jpg', 'yellow-footed-green-pigeon-381356_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Parbhani was named after Goddess Prabhavati the Goddess with Great Aura. The region didn&rsquo;t do well for itself under the Sultans, Mughals and Nizams of the Muslim Dynasty. For around 650 years, Parbhani stayed a stagnated village. However, once it was merged with Maharashtra in 1960, the place started to prosper. Parbhani is most famous for being the holy site of Sai Baba&rsquo;s a reincarnation of Dattatraya birth at a place called Pathri, about 45 kms away. The Jabareshwar Beleshwar Mahadev, the Mota Maruthi and the Pardeshwara are few of the many religious shrines that can be found here. The Jain Temple of Jintur is another fantastic holy spot 40 kms away. A village nearby that goes by the name Mudgal is said to be the only place where Lord Vishnu and Lord Shiva are worshipped together. The Narsimha Temple is another famous temple here. The temple of Shri Keshavraj Babasaheb deserves special mention, as he was Shri Sai Baba&rsquo;s Guruji. This temple is located at Selu, about 45 kilometres away from Parbhani. Earlier known as Parbhavatinagar, Parbhani is a district located in the state of Maharashtra. It figures as one amongst the eight districts of the Marathwada region. It is set at an altitude of 357 mts above sea level and is flanked by the Balaghat Hills and the Ajanta Hills on either side. Parbhani has religious significance in Hindu Mythology. It is a birthplace of saints, Sai Baba being one of the most celebrated and revered ones. There are numerous temples situated in the nearby vicinity.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The city of Parbhani is equipped with decent staying options which include luxurious lodges, economy to budget hotels and guesthouses. MTDC provides 3 double bedded rooms with restaurant facilities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\n<strong>By Air</strong> - The Nanded Domestic Airport is the closest domestic airport to Parbhani about 60 kms away. The flights operating from this airport is fairly regular about four days a week.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Parbhani is well accessible by rail from many major cities and towns within and outside the state of Maharashtra. There are daily, regular trains that connect Parbhani to cities like Mumbai, Pune, Hyderabad, Delhi and Nashik.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- There are several Private Tour Operators and state transport buses that ply between Parbhani and various other cities in Maharashtra like Mumbai and Pune. Private Buses generally pose as a better alternative to state owned transport services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - State highways and roads from the district headquarters at Parbhani connect all nine sub districts and major towns.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - NEW AISHWARYA RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT BESIDES SBI, BASMAT RD, INDUSTRIAL AREA - (FAMOUS FOR DAL MAKHANI AND BUTTER PANEER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - MADHURBHOJ, &nbsp;LOCATED AT VASMAT ROAD, BESIDE TRUPATI MANGAL KARYALAYA - (FAMOUS FOR RAJASTHANI THALI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - NATIONAL DARBAR, LOCATED AT GANDHI PARK - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN TANDURI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - SANT KRUPA, LOCATED AT BASMAT RD, VIVEK NAGAR, EKTA COLONY&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;- (FAMOUS FOR FRUIT JUCIE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - TULSI SNACKS LOCATED AT SWAPNAPURTI, RAMKRISHNA NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - DATTAKRUPA HOTEL, LOCATED AT OPPOSITE GAUL HOSPITAL, GAWANE RD, NEW MONDHA - (FAMOUS FOR POHA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - KOLHAPURI THASKA, LOCATED AT BASMAT RD, VIVEK NAGAR, ACHARYA NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR VADAPAV AND BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>8 - TASTY BITE, IN PRABHANI - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;SNACKS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>9 - GOLI VADA PAV, IN PRABHANI - (FAMOUS FOR VADA PAV)</strong></p>\r\n', '');
