(657, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'ALIGARH', 'garcinia-cambogia-343524_1280.jpg', 'garcinia-cambogia-343524_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Aligarh is a city located in the Aligarh district of India&rsquo;s most populous state, Uttar Pradesh. The city is a significant learning centre and has many educational institutions to its credit including the famous Aligarh Muslim University. Aligarh has a long history and it is here that the battle of Ally Ghur was fought between the French and the British. Aligarh was earlier known as Kol, probably after the name of the original tribe that lived there. However, other versions have it that was named after a mountain or even a sage or demon. During the time of Mughal ruler, Ibrahim Lodhi, a fort by the name of Kol was built by Muhammad, son of Umar, who was the governor of Kol. The fort is today the main attraction of the city however it is now known as the Aligarh Fort. The city changed various hands and over the journey it was rechristened as Muhammadgarh, Sabitgarh, Ramgarh, and finally Aligarh. Apart from being a major educational centre, Aligarh is also a famous commercial centre of North India. It is the hub of the lock manufacturing industry an industry that traces its roots to Mughal period. The city is also famous for its brass products and Aligarh Pajamas which can be bought in market places in Aligarh such as Railway Road Market and Centre Point Market. The Aligarh Fort is the city&rsquo;s most famous attraction. Giving it company is the Dor Fortress, which is currently in ruins but sheds light on the period of its construction. The Aligarh Muslim University is one of the leading educational institutions in India. October to March happens to be the best time to visit Aligarh.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">One who plans to visit Aligarh should not worry about accommodation. There are a wide range of hotels including budget, economy hotels and 2 to 3 stars hotels with all sorts of modern facilities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport is New Delhi airport which is about 147 kilometres away. From Delhi, tourists can reach Aligarh by bus and train or hire a private taxi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Aligarh lies on the Delhi Kolkata Grand Chord line and is well connected to most of the cities in Uttar Pradesh and India. The main railway station in Aligarh is Aligarh Junction which is served by superfast trains.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Grand Trunk Road, India&#39;s longest and one of the oldest roads passes through Aligarh. Two national highways, NH 91 and NH 93, pass through Aligarh. Yamuna Expressway, an expressway from Delhi to Agra, is under development which passes through Aligarh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Masoodabad Bus Terminal and Gandhi Park Bus Terminal are the two main bus terminals of Aligarh from where Uttar Pradesh State Road Transport Corporation (UPSRTC) serves cities all over the states of Uttar Pradesh, Uttaranchal, Rajasthan, Madhya Pradesh and Haryana.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - ALIGARH - [FAMOUS FOR GULATTHI IS A CREAMY RICE BASED DISH ; THESE TWO DISHES ARE AVAILABLE IN A SMALL SHOP CLOSE TO DARGAH&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;FAMOUS FOR PADDEE(BEEF) KA SALAN AND GADDE KI ROTI(THICK ROTI)]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - PANDITJI, AT RUSSELANJ - (FAMOUS FOR LADDOO)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - JALAIL&#39;S, AT STATION ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR GAJAK)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - KING&#39;S, AT MARRIS ROAD MABOOD NAGAR CIVIL LINES - (FAMOUS FOR ROLLS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - DEEPAK, AT SAMAD ROAD, CENTRE POINT, SHYAM NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR SWEETS LIKE RASMALAI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - HAJI BUNDA&#39;S SHOP, AT UPPER COURT - (FAMOUS FOR EGG HALWA MADE FROM EGG YOLK)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - GOLI VADA PAV , AT RAMGHAT ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR VADA PAV)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(658, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'AZAMGARH', 'cape-honeysuckle-332296_640.jpg', 'cape-honeysuckle-332296_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Azamgarh is a town in the Indian state of Uttar Pradesh. It is headquarters of Azamgarh district and Azamgarh division. Azamgarh, one of the easternmost districts of Uttar Pradesh, once formed a part of the ancient Kosala kingdom, except its north eastern part. Azamgarh was founded in 1665. After the attack of Chabile Ram, Azmat Khan fled northwards followed by the interior forces. He attempted to cross the Ghaghra into Gorakhpur, but the people on the other side opposed his landing, and he was either shot in mid stream or was drowned in attempting to escape by swimming. In 1688 AD during Azamt&#39;s lifetime, his eldest son Ekram took part in the management of the state, and after Azam&#39;s death he was perhaps left in possession together with Mohhabat, another son. The remaining two sons were taken away and for a time detained as hostages for their brother&rsquo;s good behaviour. The successor of Ikram finally confirmed the title of his family to the Jamidari. Ikram left no heirs and was succeeded by Iradat, son of Mohhabat. But the real ruler all along had been Mohhabat, and after Ikram&#39;s death, he continued to rule in his son&#39;s name.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are average places available to stay in Azamgarh. A number of factors like promotion of tourism and rapid industrial progress have given boost to hotels catering in Azamgarh.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - There are no regular flights from other major cities of the country to Azamgarh. Nearest airport is Varanasi Airport about 82 kms away.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Azamgarh railway station is well connected to other major cities of the country via regular trains.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Tourists can easily get regular buses to Azamgarh from other major cities of the country.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - AFC RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT OPPOSITE SUKHDEV PAHALWANA SPORTS STADIUM - (FAMOUS FOR ROASTED CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - TASTE OF WORLD, LOCATED AT NEAR STATE BANK OF INDIA, RAIDOPUR - (FAMOUS FOR SANDWICH)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - SUBASH SWEETS AND TEA SHOP, LOCATED AT CHANDPUR - (FAMOUS FOR BARFII AND PEDA)&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(659, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'BAHRAICH', 'rain-lily-346836_1280.jpg', 'rain-lily-346836_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Bahraich is surrounded by lots of mythologies. In the ancient time it was termed as the capital of Lord Brahma, who created the Universe. Bahraich was also known as the part of famous Gandharva Forest. Even today North east area of several hundred square kilometres of the district is covered by the forest. It is said that Brahma ji developed this forest covered area as the place of worship for Rishis &amp; Sadhus. Therefore this place come to known as Brahmaich and later changed to Bahraich. Bahraich is a city in the state of Uttar Pradesh and is located on the Saryu River, a tributary of river Ghaghra. Bahraich got its name from the Arabic word bahr which means a large body of water. Situated on the bank of river Ghaghra, it was named Bahraich. Bahraich is a very old town of India, inhabited around the 10th century. It is believed that there was an ancient Brahma Temple here, thus giving the city the name Brahmaich, thus, Bahraich. Another belief is that Bahraich got its name from the Ashram of Mahirshi Bhar. Bahraich was the land of Rishis, Munis and Bhikhkhus. A town near Bahraich is named as Risiya Rishi Bhumi in ancient times. Bahraich is 125 kms north east of Lucknow, the state capital. The towns of Barabanki, Gonda, Balrampur, Lakheempur and Sitapur share local boundaries with Bahraich. A factor which makes this town important is the international border shared with the neighbouring country, Nepal. The climate &amp; soil of this district is extremely suitable for sericulture. Bahraich is a much undeveloped district in terms of medium and large scale Industries. Industries based on Agricultural &amp; Forest products exist here.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Hotels near Bahraich railway station Bahraich can be the choice of accommodation for comfort that comes at an easily affordable tariff. Bahraich brings a plenty of options in budget hotels so that tourists can relax after an eventful day spent exploring the places in the city.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air </strong>- Instead of Bahraich tourists can a get flight to Amausi Airport in Lucknow about 105 kms away on regular basis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - There are regular trains from other major cities of the country to Bahraich.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Bahraich is well connected to other major cities of the country via regular buses.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - RAJ SWEETS, IN CHOWK BAZAR NEAR CLOCK TOWER - (FAMOUS FOR JALEBIS AND MITHAIS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - FOOD PLAZA, NEAR GOVERNMENT INTER COLLEGE - (FAMOUS FOR NORTH INDIAN FOOD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - MAKHAN BHOG, NEAR DISTRICT HOSPITAL - (FAMOUS FOR LOCAL CUISINES)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(660, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'BANDA', 'mango-tree-253192_640.jpg', 'mango-tree-253192_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Banda is a city and a municipal board in Banda district in the state of Uttar Pradesh. Banda lies south of the Yamuna River in the Bundelkhand region. It is the administrative head quarters of Banda district. The town is well connected to major cities with railways and state highways. The town is near the right bank of the river Ken. It is bounded in the north by district of Fatehpur in the east by the district of Chitrakut in the west by the district of Hamirpur and Mahoba and in the south by Satna, Panna, and Chhatarapur the districts of adjoining Madhya Pradesh . There are mainly three rivers in the district namely Ken, Baghain and Yamuna. A number of open air performances, combining the rural style of folk music and dancing with some national theme are a regular feature of rural life in the district. Nautanki and dramas based on mythology are often staged and attract large gatherings, particularly in the villages.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Because there are only a few places to stay in Banda itself, tourists ought to make their reservations early if they are planning on staying at Banda.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - There are no regular flights from other major cities of the country to Banda. Nearest airport is Khajuraho Airport 85 kms away from Banda.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Banda Railway Station is well connected to other major cities of the country via regular trains.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Tourists can easily get regular buses to Banda from other major cities of the country.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - BASU SWEET HOUSE, AT RAILWAY STATION, GULAR NAKA - (FAMOUS FOR RASAGULLA, GULAB JAMUN AND KAJU KATLI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - RAJ KAMAL, AT GULAR NAKA - (FAMOUS FOR KULFI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - SHIVAM RESTAURANT, AT CHHOTI BAZAAR - (FAMOUS FOR PAV BHAJI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - AMIT JUICE CORNER, AT KALU KUWAN CHAURAHA - (FAMOUS FOR JUICES AND MILKSHAKES)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(661, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'BARABANKI', 'common-tailorbird-300534_640.jpg', 'common-tailorbird-300534_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">One of the four districts of Faizabad division in Uttar Pradesh Barabanki is bound by the parallel streams of the Ghagra and Gomti rivers. The district is also known as the gateway to Poorvanchal. In the days of yore, it was the penance site for several saints and ascetics. It is believed that the place was first founded in 1000 AD. Barabanki was later taken over by the Muslims and a few years down, it was divided into twelve shares and so the name. Another story goes that the place derived its name from ban, or jungle, implying twelve shares of the jungle. There is much to see and do in Barabanki. It is home to the Parijaat tree, a unisex tree, which is one of its kinds. The Barabanki Ghantaghar or clock tower acts as the entrance to the city. The Mahadeva Temple is one of the oldest in the district. Barabanki district boasts several ancient and historic towns and villages such as Satrikh, the home town of the head guru of the royal family, Dewa, famous for the shrine of Haji Waris Ali Shah, Badosarai, a famous pilgrimage centre, and Kintur, the birthplace of Kunti, the mother of the Pandavas in the epic of Mahabharata. The best period to visit is from November to March. The temperature during the rest of the months can be very high.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The city grounds numerous accommodation inns in its grounds like quality hotels, guest houses, lodges etc for the visitors of the city to stay comfortably.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest airport is in Lucknow city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train </strong>- The railway station in Barabanki is served by trains from cities such as Ahmedabad, Bareilly, Gorakhpur, Lucknow, Bangalore, Old Delhi, Amritsar and Varanasi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Barabanki is served by the buses run by the State Transport Corporation.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - FOOD JUNCTION, AT RAGHUNANDAN PLAZA BASEMENT, NEAR MUNSHI GANJ WAQLI GALI - (FAMOUS FOR BURGER, SANDWICHES AND CHOWMEIN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - UPVAN, AT BEGAM GUNJ - (FAMOUS FOR FRIED RICE, MANCHURIAN AND SAHI PANEER)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(662, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'BARAUT', 'pylon-342715_640.jpg', 'pylon-342715_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Baraut is a Town in Baraut Tehsil in Baghpat district of Uttar Pradesh. It belongs to Meerut division. It is located 20 kms towards north from district head quarters Bagpat. It is a Tehsil head quarter. Baraut is a constituency in legislative assembly of Uttar Pradesh. Baraut is known for producing wheels and axles which are used all over India in motor vehicles. The economy of this town is based on agriculture in a big way. Being a fertile land close to the Yamuna and Jamuna Rivers, the main local crops are of sugarcane, wheat and mustard, along with mangoes, grapes and guavas. Apart from business equal emphasis are also laid on education in the town making Baraut home to some of the finest educational institutions in the country. The population in the city consists of a fair mix of different religions and communities giving rise to a multilingual culture that is known for its high levels of tolerance across the country. The city and its population are strongly driven by an aptitude that helps businesses grow. In fact, the city is home to several business houses that work as partners and extended teams for leading brands across several markets. Baraut has a landscape that is a fertile ground for entrepreneurial activities materializing into big time commercial ventures. Along with this, Baraut is also home to several beautiful architectural monuments that represent the rich cultural lineage of the city. From the temples to the buildings, the city is robust with many must see places that are guaranteed to impress the tourists. Close to the banks of the Yamuna River; Baraut is majorly an agriculture driven economy.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The New Indica Hotel in Baraut is one of the finest places of accommodation in Baghpat city that is located in the prime city locality of Baraut.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport to Baraut is Indira Gandhi Intl. Airport, New Delhi which is 60 kms away from Baraut city centre.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Regular trains are available from all major cities to Baraut Railway Station. The nearest major railway station to Baraut is Sonipat railway station which is 27 kms away from Baraut city centre.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Baraut is well linked with all the major cities of the country through roadways and regular bus services.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - JAI MAA VAISHNO, AT &nbsp;BARAUT - (FAMOUS FOR FRUIT JUICES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - J. P. SWEETS, AT GHATTA BAZAAR, NAYA BAZAAR - (FAMOUS FOR LADDOO, RASMALAI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - ANAND&#39;S, NEAR SHEEL HOSPITAL - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN SOUP)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(663, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'BAREILLY', 'highway-204148_6402.jpg', 'highway-204148_6403.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Located in the Bareilly district of Uttar Pradesh Bareilly is a major commercial centre of north India. It is known for its many temples and religious sites located across the city. Located on the Ramganga River, it is also home to some interesting museums and amusement parks. Bareilly is also a major centre for the manufacturing of furniture, more specifically cane furniture. This city is also known as Bans Bareilly. Though bans literally mean cane, the city is not named after bans but after two, princes, Bansaldev and Baraldev, sons of Jagat Singh Katehriya who founded the city in 1537. As said above, Bareilly is known for its temples notably the four Shiva temples namely Dopeswarnath, Madhinath, Trivatinath and Alaknath, located in the four corners of the city. The Lakshmi Narayan Temple is also worth visiting. Bareilly also has a famous amusement park by the name of Fun City and is a great place to enjoy some water slides and a family picnic. Some other religious site includes the Dargah-e-Ala-Hazrat, Bibi Ji ki Masjid, and Sri Sai Mandi. Those who are interested in the history of the city can visit the Panchala Museum and the Army Service Corps Museum. The ideal time to visit Bareilly is during the winter months.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The famous Indian city of Bareilly offers sufficient accommodation options to travellers. There is long list of hotels and one can choose from both governments approved and diverse other hotels in Bareilly. Some of the famous hotels in the Bareilly include Civil &amp; Military Hotel which is around 3 kilometres from the airport and just 1 kilometre from bus stand and many others from which tourists can select as per their need and demand.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport is New Delhi airport which is about 271 kms. From here, tourists can take a public/private transport bus, hire a cab, or take a train to reach Bareilly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Bareilly lies on the Delhi Kolkata line and is well connected to major destinations in Uttar Pradesh and other major cities in India. Bareilly Cantonment Junction is the main railway station in the town.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- The town is linked to other cities in UP and neighbouring states by a network of National and State Highways. Both public and private companies ply buses to and fro from cities such as Jaipur, Agra, Mathura, Ghaziabad, New Delhi, Lucknow and Varanasi.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - BAREILLY - [FAMOUS FOR NAHARI &nbsp;IS A DISH PREPARED FROM THE BONES OF THE GOAT ; SEEKH KEBAB IS ASPECIALITY OF BAREILLY THAT ARE PREPARED WITH MINCED MEAT OF LAMB AND IS MIXED HERBS AND SPICES]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - CHHOTELAL, AT AYUB KHAN CHOWRAHA - [FAMOUS FOR AALOO KI TIKKI, PAPADI AND MOONG KI DAL KA CHEELRA]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - BIKANERI - (FAMOUS FOR JALEBI, RABARI, RASMALI, RASGULLA, GULAB JAMUN AND MILKCAKE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - KIPPS CHAAT CORNER, AT CIVIL LINCE MARKET - (FAMOUS FOR AALOO TIKKI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - CRAZY POINT, AT CIVIL LINCE MARKET - (FAMOUS FOR PAV BHAAJI, CHOWMEIN, CHILLY CHEESE, FRIED RICE AND MACARONI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - FERN&#39;S BAKERY - (FAMOUS FOR MUTTON AND CHICKEN PATTIES AND VEG PATTIES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - TOLARAM, AT PUNJABI MARKET - (FAMOUS FOR KULFI)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(664, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'BASTI', 'india-77848_640.jpg', 'india-77848_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Basti a town located in the Basti district of Uttar Pradesh has in the ancient period, been ruled by several dynasties, many of whom have left an indelible mark on the cultural fabric of the region. The town of Basti which officially came into existence in 1865 is covered with bamboo forests and mango groves. In fact, Basti is encompassed by thick vegetation which provides a welcome relief from the hustle and bustle of town activity. Basti has several attractions to its credit including the Chando Tal which is a popular picnic site. Another interesting place is the Barah village near Basti. The small village finds mention in works of mythology, and there is an old temple dedicated to Lord Shiva which is located here. The Badeshwarnath Temple located on the banks of the River Kuwana also attracts visitors. Basti is well connected by air, rail and road. The ideal time to visit Basti is between November and March.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">There are several budget hotels, govt. guest houses and paying guest house facilities available in Basti.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport is Lucknow airport. From here, tourists can take a taxi or bus to Basti.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Train</strong> - The town of Basti has a railway station of its own and there are frequent train services from many places around the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Road</strong> - The place is located around 196 kms from the city of Lucknow. Services of local and UPSRTC bus services are available to move to Basti from the nearby and major cities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(665, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'BIJNOR', 'datura-172533_640.jpg', 'datura-172533_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Bijnor, also called as Bijnaur, Bijnour is the capital city of Bijnor district in Uttar Pradesh and also a municipal board. India also called as Bharat was named after the mighty Emperor Bharatha who was born in Bijnor. King Bharatha ruled almost all parts of India, under whose kingdom the happiness flourished among the people. King Bharatha spends his early childhood days in Bijnor district. Bijnor district is bounded by river Ganga and Ramganga on its borders. Bijnor was formerly a part of Mughal Empire commanded by Emperor Akbar. By the 18th century, the Rohilla Pashtuns gained their freedom from the Mughals and established their rule in Bijnor which was overthrown by the Marathas. Rohillas waited for their opportunity to win the Marathas and to retain their powers back in Bijnor. By 1772, the Rohillas made a treaty with the Nawab of Oudh to sack the Marathas out of their place in exchange of money, the Nawab of Oudh was successful in expelling the Marathas and placing the Rohillas in power, but the Rohillas leaders failed to pay the Nawab of Oudh the agreed sum of money, so in 1774 the Nawab of Oudh with the help of British East India company sacked Rohillas rule beyond the Ganges and established his rule in Bijnor, however, in the very same year the Nawab of Oudh gave up his powers on Bijnor to the British East India company which ruled Bijnor and its fellow parts till 1857 after which the Nawad of Najibabad established their rule, unfortunately next year the Nawab of Najibabad was overthrown by the British East India company. From 1858 till the Indian Independence Bijnor was under the rule of East India Company.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The hotels in Bijnor provide quality stay for customers. The various facilities provided in the hotel are accommodation, parking facility, room service, travel facility and many more. The charges are very reasonable for the quality of service provided by the hotels. The tourist spots in Bijnor can be reached without hassle from these hotels.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Muzaffarnagar airport in Muzaffarnagar and the Jolly Grand airport in Dehradun are the two nearest airports from Bijnor at a distance of 44.67 kms and 89.43 kms respectively from Bijnor.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Bijnor railway station facilitates train transport from Bijnor to most of the parts of the nation and ticket reserving facility is also available within the railway station premise. The railway station also links the famous tourist destinations nearby Bijnor.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - The state and the national highways aid the travel through road to and from Bijnor. National highway 119 connects Bijnor city with other states of the nation. The maintenance and repair of the roadways and the railways are monitored by the government. Uttar Pradesh state Road transport corporation UPSRTC provides quality buses which runs through Bijnor and its major neighbouring cities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - TULAARAM MISTHAN BHANDAR, NEAR RAILWAY STATION, NH 74, HARIDWAR ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;SAMOSAS AND GULAB JAMUN)<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(666, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'BUDAUN', 'zimbabwe-creeper-336970_1280.jpg', 'zimbabwe-creeper-336970_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Budaun district is one of the districts of Uttar Pradesh state of India, and Budaun town is the district headquarters. Budaun district is a part of Bareilly division. Budaun is holy land of Great Sufi Saint&#39;s, Auliya, Wali and Peer&#39;s as well as a place of izarat&#39;s. It is very holy place in the India. According to Prof. Goti John this city was named Bedamooth in an ancient inscription which is now in Lucknow Musium. In that Period this pradesh was known as Panchal. According to a line of that Stone Writeup there was a village Bhadaunlak near it. Muslim Historian Mr. Roz Khan Lodhi said that King Ashoka Built a Buddh Vihar &amp; Kila and he named it BuddhMau. Geographically Budaun city is located near Holy River Ganga, at an average elevation of 169 mts above sea level. Length of the district is 144 kms and width is 60 kms and total area of district is 5168 sq kms. Budaun city is 235 kms from Delhi and 311 kms from Lucknow.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Budaun offers with low to medium range hotels and dharamshalas. One can choose from these options according to their budget.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Instead of Badaun tourists can a get flight to Kheria Airport, Agra about 149 kms from Badaun on regular basis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- There are regular trains from Badaun railway station to other major cities of the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Badaun does not have a bus stand. Nearest option is Bareilly.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - PIZZA FACTORY WORLD, LOCATED AT NEAR UNION BANK, INDRA CHOWK, CIVIL LINES - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - RADHIKA SWEETS, LOCATED AT INDRA CHOWK, CIVIL LINES - (FAMOUS FOR GULAB JAMUN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - HARI RAM &nbsp;BHANDAR, LOCATED AT KATRABRAHMPUR - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA AND JALEBI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - PANNA&#39;S, &nbsp;LOCATED AT HALWAI BAZAR, SARAFA MARKET - (FAMOUS FOR CHAAT ITEMS LIKE PANNIPURI, ALOO TIKKI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - NAINA SWEETS, LOCATED AT SH 33, BUDAUN - (FAMOUS FOR KAJU BARFI)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(667, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'BULANDSHAHR', 'highway-332365_6402.jpg', 'highway-332365_6403.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Bulandshahr is a city in the Bulandshahr district of Uttar Pradesh and is also its administrative headquarters. The region traces its roots to the Mahabharata period. Several excavations carried out here have revealed ancient coins and artefacts that are now preserved in the Lucknow Museum. The history of Bulandshahr district begins much before 1200 BC. The region is located in proximity to Hastinapur, which was the capital of the Pandavas. After the decline of Hastinapur, another place by the name of Ahar, which is located in the north east part of the Bulandshahr district gained centre stage. Much later, King Parma added a fort in this part of the region. Over a period, a Tomar king laid the foundation of another fort called Baran and established his capital. The kingdom of Baran came to an end during the 12th century. In 1192, Mughal conqueror Muhammad Ghauri conquered several parts of India including the fort of Barn. The city of Barn changed several hands and finally came to be known as Bulandshahr. The word Bulandshahr has Persian origins and translates to high city. As said above, the history of Bulandshahr goes back to ancient times, and there are several ruins found throughout the district in places such as Bhatora Veerpur, and Ghalibpur. Some of the places of interest include Chola, Ahar, and Valipura. Chola is a small village famous for the Bibcol Chola Polio Vaccine factory. Karnavas holds great historical significance and is named after the great Mahabharata hero, Karna. Vallipura is a small scenic village located on the banks of a river and has the Van Chetna Kendra Centre as its main point of interest. The best time to visit is between November and April.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Bulandshahr offers a wide range of accommodations from guest houses, resorts, budget hotel to luxury hotels. The best luxury hotels, available in this city, are the Mud Fort and the Fort.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport is the New Delhi airport which is about 80 kms away. Regular taxis ply from the airport to Bulandshahr.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- The Bulandshahr railway station receives trains from major parts of the country including Delhi, Kolkatta, Varanasi and Mathura.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Bulandshahr is well connected by National Highway 91 and state highway 14 and 18.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Buses run by the Uttar Pradesh Transport Corporation and Delhi Transport Corporation serve the city. Private luxury buses to Bulandshahr from Delhi and other cities are also available.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Within Bulandshahr, tourists can take the local buses or travel around in rickshaws and local buses.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SACHIN FAMILY DHABA, AT BULANDSHAHAR-KHURJA ROAD NATIONAL HIGHAY 91 - (FAMOUS FOR MISSI ROTI AND KADHAI PANEER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - PYAREY LAL SWEETS, AT GHANDHI CHOWK, DEVI MANDIR WALI GALI - (FAMOUS FOR SOHAN PAPADI, GULAB JAMMUN AND JALEBI)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(668, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'CHANDAULI', 'lagoons-of-ruidera-426295_640.jpg', 'lagoons-of-ruidera-426295_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The Chandauli district is located about 50 kms from Varanasi in Uttar Pradesh. It is named after Chandra Sah, a Barhaulia Rajput of the family of Narotam Rai who founded the city. A fort was later built by his descendants. Though in ruins, the fort still attracts a fair number of visitors. Chandauli has several tourist places to its credit including Hakiya Kali Mandir and Baba Latifshah Tomb. However, its main claim to fame is the Chandauli Wildlife Sanctuary. One of the lesser known sanctuaries in India, it is nonetheless home to several interesting species of animals, birds and plants. Away from mass tourism, it retains its pristine charm. It was established to conserve the Asiatic lions, and though their numbers have more or less dwindled, the sanctuary plays home to several other animals and birds. There are several picnic sites and dense forests within the sanctuary. The ideal time to visit Chandauli is between October and March.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><br />\r\nThere are some decent options for accommodation available in Chandauli. On can alternatively, also stay at Mughalsarai.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport is at Varanasi which is about 50 kms away. From here, tourists can hire a taxi or take a bus to reach Chandauli.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - The Chandauli Railway Station is on the Mughal Sarai Sasaram line. It is served by trains from major Indian cities such as Delhi, Varanasi, Kolkata and Agra.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Tourists can easily get regular buses to Chandauli from other major cities of the country.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - AAKASH GANGA RESTAURANT AND SWEET HOUSE,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT GRAND TRUNK ROAD, OPPOSITE DISTRICT COURT - (FAMOUS FOR PANEER DOSA)\\</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - RAMLAL, LOCATED AT GANGA ROAD, GAUTAM NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR GULAB JAMUN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - GOKUL SWEETS, LOCATED AT GAUTAM NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR VARITIES OF SWEETS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - VINDHYA SAROVER BAKERY, LOCATED AT WARD NO.14, LOHIA NAGAR, NAGAR PANCHAYAT - (FAMOUS FOR CAKE&#39;S AND COOKIES)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(669, 14, 31, 744, 'Madhya Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'CHITRAKOOT', 'lemon-tree-272614_1280.jpg', 'lemon-tree-272614_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Chitrakoot is a small town situated in the north Vindhyan range. Legends have it that Chitrakoot was the place where Lord Rama, his wife Sita and his brother Lakshmana stayed for eleven and half of their fourteen years of exile. Chitrakoot is located over the districts of Chitrakoot in Uttar Pradesh and Satna in Madhya Pradesh. Chitrakoot holds great importance according to Hindu mythology and the epic Ramayana. According to Ramayana, Chitrakoot was the place where Bharata, brother of Ram came to visit Ram and ask him to come back to Ayodhya and rule the kingdom. It is also believed that the principal gods of Hindus took incarnations here. This divine city is also known as the hill of many wonders and it totally justifies the name. Chitrakoot mountain range has numerous places of great religious importance like Bharat Milap Temple, Hanuman Dhara, Janki Kund and much more. It is indeed the gift of nature and the gods. This is the place where Goswami Tulsidas, author of the Ramcharitmanas, spent many years of his life. There are many lively fairs which are organized on different occasions and festivals. Overall, Chitrakoot is a perfect blend of divinity, serenity, and an exquisite beauty.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">As a popular tourist town, Chitrakoot has a lot of budget&nbsp;as well as luxury accommodation options available. Ramghat is the most important area for the tourists and it&rsquo;s advisable to get a place there.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Bamrauli airport at Allahabad is the nearest airport about 106 kms away from Chitrakoot that connects Chitrakoot to the rest of India.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Regular bus services ply to and fro the city of Chitrakoot. They operate on a daily basis, through a well connected network of state highways and NH 76.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Chitrakoot Dham is the nearest railway station in Karwi, Chitrakoot, which connects the town to the rest of India by rail.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Roads here are well connected as the tourism is a major source of income for people here. Tourists can easily get buses, taxis or rickshaws in the locality.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SAMRAT DHABA, LOCATED AT NEAR CHANDNI DHABA, BEDIPULIA, CHITRAKOOT DHAM, KARWI - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN CURRY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - GUNJAN SWEET HOUSE, LOCATED AT ALLAHABAD BANDA HIGHWAY ROAD, IN FRONT OF POLICE STATION, BADAUSA - (FAMOUS FOR MILK CAKE IS A TYPE OF DESERT)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(670, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'ETAWAH', 'champa-346329_1280.jpg', 'champa-346329_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Located on the left bank of the River Yamuna, Etawah is situated in the state of Uttar Pradesh and is one of the 75 districts of the Kanpur Division. The city reveals an outstanding range of surface and scenery. The bigger part lies within the Doab or level alluvial plain in between the Ganges and the Yamuna. Etawah Travel Guide is incomplete without a mention of its rich heritage. It was a centre for the revolt of 1857, Allan Octavian Hume being the promoter of Indian National Congress was the district collector. It is also a place of convergence between Yamuna and Chambal. It has experienced innovation and advancement under British rule and in the period of post independence.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The hotels in Etawah are found across the heavily crowded commercial neighbourhoods of Etawah. These Etawah hotels offer accommodation to the visitors in the city at the most affordable prices. Basic amenities like food, television in room, attached bathrooms and 24 hour room service are available at the hotels in Etawah.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest Domestic Airport is Gwalior Airport; roughly one and half hour drive from the city and is well connected with the cities like Indore, Bhopal, Delhi, Agra, Mumbai, Jaipur and Varanasi etc. The nearest International Airport is Chaudhary Charan Singh Airport, Lucknow, roughly 229 kms from Etawah.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Etawah has its own Railhead known as Etawah Railway Station and it is well connected with the major cities of state like Ambikapur, Karonji, Barwadih, Garhwa and Hatia. It lies on Delhi Kolkata line.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Etawah is connected to other cities through Uttar Pradesh State Road Transport Corporation (UPSRTC) and some private travel services.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - PANCHU, AT CIVIL LINES - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSAS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - KALU, AT CHOGURJEE NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR KAUCHARI)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(671, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'FAIZABAD', 'ayodhya-nagri-884352_6401.jpg', 'ayodhya-nagri-884352_6402.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Faizabad, in the state of Uttar Pradesh is situated on the banks of River Ghaghra, a small tributary of the River Ganga. This medium sized, overgrown town was founded in 1730 by the Nawab of Bengal, Ali Vardi Khan. Some years later, it was declared the capital of the Awadh region by Shuja-ud-daula. The town flourished under his rule and even today, Faizabad retains its colourful past which it proudly exhibits to its visitors. The nawabs built several artistically ornate buildings, many of which stand today resplendent in their glory. The city was known all over the country for its gardens, palaces, markets, roads and other infrastructure. The whole Faizabad region thrived under Nawab Shuja-ud-Daula and attained supreme glory. But after few years the capital of Awadh was shifted to Lucknow from Faizabad. The eminence and prosperity faded but the magnificent history of the region has left an ineffable mark on the city. Faizabad Travel guide provides you with an opportunity to know more about the city. Apart from its history, the city is also famous for having proximity to the most religious city Ayodhya, which is the birth place of Lord Ram, the prominent Hindu deity. The city itself boasts a huge assortment of attractive places and is also known for its hospitality. Major attractions in Faizabad include Gulab Bari, Bahu Begum Ka Maqbara, Company Gardens and many others.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The city offers the best accommodation for each class that is from cheap budget hotels to luxury hotels. As the tourists flock the city throughout the year to visit its historic monuments, it is advisable to book economy class rooms in good hotels in advance. Luxury hotels even offer personal valets and tour guides. Hotels located near the Chowk area are favoured because of their proximity to the city&rsquo;s major market and shopping centres.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - Lucknow Airport is the nearest domestic airport at a distance of around 130 kms from the heart of Faizabad. One can avail the facility of taxis and UPSRTC buses to reach Faizabad city from Lucknow airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - Faizabad railway station connects to various prominent cities within the country like Delhi, Varanasi, Allahabad, Kolkata, Kanpur, Indore, Jammu and many others. One can take local autos or cycle rickshaws to commute.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Faizabad is situated on National Highway 28 and has good connectivity with Lucknow, Varanasi, Allahabad and Gorakhpur. SH 9 and SH 15 are the nearest connecting state highways. Both public and private buses are available at Faizabad.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Bus</strong> - The state government&#39;s Road Transport Service (UPSRTC) runs regular and frequent buses to and fro from this city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - AVANTIKA TASTY BITES,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT 55, CIVIL LINES - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;PANEER BUTTER MASALA WITH BUTTER NAAN AND CHILLI POTATO)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - RAM AASARE BHANDAR, LOCATED AT IN FRONT OF SHYAMSUNDAR DHARAMSALA, CITY STATION ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR PEDE AND RABDI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - PARAM&#39;S, LOCATED AT NEAR REKABGANJ - (FAMOUS FOR CAKES, PASTRY AND BISCUITS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - MADHUR SWEET HOUSE, LOCATED AT GHANTA GHAR-GUDRI BAZAAR ROAD, NARENDRA DEV NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR MOTICHOOR LADOO)&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(672, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'FIROZABAD', 'AA68.jpg', 'AA69.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Firozabad is a city in India, in the state of Uttar Pradesh. The ancient name of this town was Chandwar nagar; it is said that once in reign of Akbar the great, revenue was being brought through the city. It was looted by the people who lived here. Akbar when came across it sent his army comprising an unch named Firoz to make the city a cantonment to improve thieves who lived here. The tomb of this firoz is still present near bus stand, today also. From the earliest it was famous for glass and bangle works, and its related small scale industry is famous throughout the world. Due to underdeveloped industry, literacy rates are very low. The landowner of Firozabad sayed, manihar, Pathan and Hindu Rajpoot castes Firozabad is located in north central India, in western Uttar Pradesh, at the northern edge of the Deccan Plateau. The height above sea level is 164 meters. The boundaries of Firozabad district touch Etah district in north and Mainpuri and Etawah districts in the east. The Yamuna River makes its southern boundary. The city is also an important market centre. It has severe winter and summer seasons. The district is mostly flat and its slope is from northwest to south.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">In Firozabad tourists can find budget hotels as well as guest houses. The city has also got well organised bread and breakfast. All the hotels in Firozabad are fully equipped with all the modern facilities and amenities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- The airport nearby Firozabad is Kheria Airport in Agra.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train&nbsp;</strong>- Trains can be taken to the railway station in Firozabad directly, and these will charge fares that are minimal and nominal. This is a good option, but tickets need to be booked in advance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - The roadway transportation is extremely developed in Firozabad. This city is closely located to the National highways like NH 24, NH 28, NH 25 and NH 56. The connectivity within Firozabad is extremely smooth due to well maintained roads. The bus services here is regulated and operated by Uttar Pradesh State Road Transport Corporation (UPSRTC).</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - The roads are more or less well maintained and the people have multiple options to commute from one place to another in Firozabad. The existing mode of transport includes buses, taxis, auto rickshaws, etc but people can also avail the facility of railway transportation because the local network is well developed here.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SHIVAM SWEET HOUSE, LOCATED AT BYE PASS ROAD, C.M MARKET, OPPOSITE GOPAL ASHRAM, ADARASH NAGAR, GANDHI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR GUJHIYA, GULAB JAMUN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - SAM SHAHAB, LOCATED AT JALESAR ROAD, VIBHAB NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - D.G., LOCATED AT KOTLA ROAD, SOHAN MARKET,NEAR MATA WALA BAGH, GANDHI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR DHOKLA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - JAI GANGEY MAIYYA, LOCATED AT NH 2, OPPOSITE BUS STAND, NEAR KUNJILAL KI BAGICHI, COMAPNY BAAG, SUHAG NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORI WITH CHOOLE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - FIROZABAD - (FAMOUS FOR HALEEM IS A STEW MADE FROM WHEAT, BARLEY, LENTILS, MEAT)</strong></p>\r\n', '');
