(673, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'GHAZIPUR', 'chicks-344299_640.jpg', 'chicks-344299_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Ghazipur or Ghazipur city, previously spelt Ghazeepore, is a city and a municipal corporation and headquarter of Ghazipur district in the state of Uttar Pradesh. It is the administrative head quarters of Ghazipur division and sub division. Back to the past, it was a place of administration under Guptas dynasty too than earlier as described in Hindu Mythology, as kingdom of King Vishwamitra, who later changed into saint and popularly known as Maharshi Vishwamitra. Vishwamitra was the son of Gaadhi. Ghazipur is famous for its opium factory, which is the largest legal opium factory in the world, started by British East India Company in 1820. It is home to handloom weaving and a perfume industry. The town is an important agricultural market. Lord Cornwallis, governor general of British India, died in Ghazipur and is buried there. The town is very close to the UP Bihar border. A historical city full of traditional substance of Syed Masood ruled till 1330. Earlier the city was known as Gadhipuri, though later it was changed to Ghazipur. Spend beautiful time of evening at Ghats and hear the noise created by water of river Ganga. &nbsp;Tourism in Ghazipur offers visits to various places having historical and religious importance and a memorable and enriching experience to the travellers. The tourism options offered by Ghazipur district attract people from all corners of the country.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There is value for money accommodation options available in Ghazipur with the highest level of guest satisfaction.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Ghazipur railway station is connected to major North Eastern cities of India.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>&nbsp;- Airport at Andhau is another good method to reach the Ghazipur city. This airport is only 9 kms away from Ghazipur. However, limited flights and VIP plans are only allowed to land in this airport. The biggest airport is in Varanasi that is only 90 kms far from Ghazipur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water</strong> - Ganga is the big river and a port of Ghazipur is connected to Haldia and Allahabad so tourists can reach Ghazipur through water as well.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Ghazipur is the big city of Uttar Pradesh and it is properly connected to various parts of the nation through road. Buses and private taxis are available from Shastrinagar, Mahua Baag, Rajdepur, Varanasi, Delhi and some more cities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - CHAURASIYA FAST FOOD, LOCATED AT MISHRA BAZAR, AAMGHAT - (FAMOUS FOR DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - AGRAWAL FAST FOOD CORNER, LOCATED AT SABJI MANDI, BARBARAHANA - (FAMOUS FOR VEGETARIAN FOOD AND MASALA COLD DRINKS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - KOLKATA FOOD CORNER, LOCATED AT 6, DLN ROAD, WARD NUMBER 1, FATEHPUR DILDAR NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR PATISHAPTA IS A DESSERT STUFFED WITH COCONUT AND FILLED WITH JAGGERY&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - NEELKANTH, LOCATED AT 4, MALGODAM RD, LANKA - (FAMOUS FOR MUZAFFAR (VERMICELLI FRIED IN GHEE AND GARNISHED WITH ALMONDS AND SAFFRON)</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(674, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'HARDOI', 'lily-790273_640.jpg', 'lily-790273_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Hardoi is a city in Uttar Pradesh with historical significance and a diverse religious population. Hardoi city is part of the greater Hardoi district, Hardoi being one of the five tehsils of the district. The Hardoi district has dense forest covering nearly 5 km, and the Ganga River&rsquo;s tributaries as well as the mighty Ganga River, flowing on the south of the district. Hardoi&#39;s tourist places include something for everybody; for the religious there&#39;s the Jama Masjid Shahabad, Hardoi Baba Temple, and the Mangala Devi Temple. For nature lovers, one of the attractions in Hardoi is the Sandi Bird Sanctuary, which is around 20 kms from Hardoi. The migratory birds arrive here in the winter and the sight of them would take anyone&#39;s breath away. The Naimisha Forest is another Hardoi tourist place for nature lovers and history lovers as it is believed to be an ancient forest mentioned in the Ramayana and is a dense forest. The combination of nature&#39;s beauty and beautiful religious shrines and temples make Hardoi a tourist place for the entire family.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The hotels in Hardoi make certain a cosy stay with orderly rooms and excellent amenities. Making longer stays comfortable in Hardoi 4 star hotel facilities for long stay are also available here.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\n<strong>By Air </strong>- Hardoi does not have an airport, and the nearest airports are the Amausi Airport in Lucknow, which is 100 kms from Hardoi, and the Kanpur Airport, which is 108 kms from Hardoi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Hardoi has several trains which stop briefly at the Hardoi Railway Station, which connects Hardoi with New Delhi, Lucknow, Chandigarh, Kolkata, and several other cities. Trains like the Doon Express, Triveni Express, and Lucknow Mail halt at the station.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Hardoi has good connectivity by bus to other parts of Uttar Pradesh and the neighbouring states as well. The Uttar Pradesh State Road Transport Corporation (UPSRTC) plies several Deluxe, AC, and Standard buses from Hardoi to other cities in the region. Hardoi has an Inter State Bus Terminal, where buses from Hardoi travel to other states, and where one can hop on a bus easily to travel to and from Hardoi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - To travel within the city, tourists can hop on any of the government buses that ply the city or take private buses. One can also travel by auto rickshaws, which are available aplenty on the streets of Hardoi. OMC Power, a power company in Hardoi, rents out Electric Bikes on a daily basis for the locals and tourists who visit the Hardoi region.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - MIRCHCHARAM, AT CINEMA ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR PANI PURI AND DAHI VADA)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(675, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'JAUNPUR', 'sorghum-273624_640.jpg', 'sorghum-273624_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Jaunpur is a city in Jaunpur district in Uttar Pradesh. The history of the region dates to 1359 when it was known as Sheeraz-e-Hind. It was founded by Feroz Shah Tughlaq. Modern day Jaunpur has yet to taste the fruits of the economic growth being witnessed by the rest of the country. However, Jaunpur tourism sports historical and holy sites that attract visitors throughout the year. Jaunpur tourism is packed with several interesting monuments, museums and holy places that attract thousands of visitors every year from all corners of the country. One such tourist place is the Shahi Bridge also known as Mughal Bridge, Akbari Bridge or Munim Khan&rsquo;s Bridge. It is one of the few important landmarks of Mughal style architecture currently existing in Jaunpur. The Shahi Quila located close to the Shahi Bridge on the Gomti River has a chequered history. It has been built on the site and by using the materials of a temple that was destroyed by the Mughal invaders. The Atala Masjid was also built after a temple by the same name was destroyed. The best time to visit Jaunpur is from November to February.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Hotels at Jaunpur offer your choice of accommodation, dine-in experience and business conveniences. There are 3 stars, 4 star and 5 star Luxury hotels at cheap and budget rate hotels available in Jaunpur.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Jaunpur does not have an airport. Tourists can take a flight to Delhi and from there travel to the city via bus or train.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Jaunpur is well connected to all major cities of India through three major railway stations: Jaunpur City Station, Shahganj Junction, and Kerakat Station. There are daily trains from Delhi and Mumbai.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Jaunpur is well connected to major towns and cities in Uttar Pradesh such as Lucknow, Varanasi, and Allahabad. NH 56, SH 36 connects all major cities to Jaunpur.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - JHAGADU HALWAI - (FAMOUS FOR PAPADI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - ANUPAM JALPAN, IN HUSAINABAD, NEAR &nbsp;T.D.COLLEGE - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA WITH MAKKHAN TOAST)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - FOODIE, NEAR NAGAR PALIKA, KOTWALI - (FAMOUS FOR SATTU KE PARATHE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - FOI, AT CITY TOWER ,GROUND FLOOR, WAZID PUR TIRAHA - (FAMOUS FOR ICECREAM, PIZZA AND CHOCOLATE SHAKE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - BENIRAM PYARELAL, TILAKDHARI COLLEGE ROAD, OLANDGAN - [FAMOUS FOR IMIRTI AND BUTTERMILK(LASSAI)]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - YADAV, AT MAIN ROAD, LOHA MANDI, SHAHGANJ - (FAMOUS FOR ICECREAM)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(676, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'JHANSI', 'rose-ringed-parakeet-380667_640.jpg', 'rose-ringed-parakeet-380667_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Jhansi is considered to be the gateway of the Bundelkhand region of Uttar Pradesh. It rose to glory during the rule of Chandelas but lost some of its sheen after the decline of their empire somewhere in the 11th century. It once again rose to prominence during the reign of Raja Bir Singh Deo in the 17th century the raja was considered to be close to Mughal Emperor Jehangir. Jhansi&rsquo;s main claim to fame is its fiery queen Rani Laxmibai, who led the forces against the British in the first battle for independence in 1857. She was married to Raja Gangadhar of Jhansi but never bore him any children, a fact that was exploited by the British who wanted to force her into retirement but she retaliated in 1857 by trying to seize the Jhansi Fort. In the battle that ensued she was able to escape with her adopted son and was on her way to join the army at Gwalior when she met her death. She is widely regarded as the John of Arc of India. History apart, Jhansi is now also famous for the Jhansi Festival, which is held every year in February March. Most of the attractions found in Jhansi are historical in nature. The main draw is the magnificent Fort of Jhansi which was the venue of the battle between Rani Laxmibai and the British forces. Located nearby is Chirgoan which was the birthplace of the famous poet, Maithili Sharan Gupta. Orchha is famous for its fort while St. Jude&rsquo;s Shrine, situated on Civil Lines in Jhansi, is also a popular tourist destination for the Catholic Christians. The recently introduced Jhansi Mahotsav gives the opportunity to enjoy the arts and crafts of the region. November to March happens to be the best time to visit Jhansi.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Jhansi being a popular tourist hub has various 3 star hotel options that make your stay here a memorable one. All the modern amenities such as free Wi-Fi pick up and drop facility from the airport/railway station, laundry facilities, in-house dining facilities are available in most of the luxury hotels in the city. Besides, they are all centrally located and close to most of the landmarks of the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport is Gwalior Airport is about 98 kilometres away. From here, tourists can take the public transport bus or hire a taxi to reach Jhansi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Jhansi is well connected to the other major cities of India by an excellent railway network. The nearest railhead is the Jhansi Cantonment Railway Station. It is served by the fastest luxury trains in India including Shatabadi Express.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Jhansi is linked to major cities of Uttar Pradesh and other cities by National Highways 25 and 26.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - The city bus stand at Talpura is located on the main Jhansi Kanpur highway. Passengers travelling Gwalior, Agra, Jaipur, can alight either at BKD Chowraha or Elite Crossing. Both the U.P. State Roadways Corporation as well as M.P. State Roadways Corporation has bus service around Jhansi. Luxury buses by private operators ply on select routes; be it short or long distance travel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Buses, rickshaws, tempos and cars are the best way for travel within the city and its neighbouring villages. While tempos and buses offer cheapest mode of transport, rickshaws and cars are relatively pricey.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - DELHI WALLA CHAT, AT MAIN CHOWK - (FAMOUS FOR PANIPURIS AND AALOO TIKKI)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">2 - SHRINATH, SADAR BAZAAR - (FAMOUS FOR PAV BHAAJI, PULAO AND MILKSHAKES)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">3 - JODHPUR MITHAI BHANDAR, AT SADAR BAZAAR - (FAMOUS FOR JODHPURI KACHORI, MILKSHAKES AND SNACKS ITEMS)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">4 - NARAYAN CHAT BHANDAR, AT SADAR BAZAAR - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;AALOO-TIKKI(VEG CUTLET), DAHIVADA AND PAANIPURI)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">5 - GEETA BHOJNALAYA, AT ELITE SQUARE - (FAMOUS FOR PANEER BUTTER MASALA, DAL BUTTER FRY AND TANDORI PARATHA)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">6 - NAVBHARAT BAKERY SHOP, AT SADAR BAZAAR - (FAMOUS FOR BURGERS, SANDWICHES, ICECREAMS AND MASALA COLD DRINKS)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">7 - SNACKS KIOSKS, AT SADAR BAZAAR - (FAMOUS FOR CHINESE AND INDIAN FAST FOODS)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">8 - JANAK&#39;S, &nbsp;AT ELITE SQUARE - (FAMOUS FOR VEGETARIAN FOOD AND SWEETS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(677, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'KUSHINAGAR', 'reclining-buddha-1514012_640.png', 'reclining-buddha-1514012_6401.png', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kushinagar is an important Buddhist pilgrimage town in Uttar Pradesh. According to Buddhist scriptures, it is here near the Hiranyavati River that Gautama Buddha attained Parinirvana after his death. It was known as Kushavati in the days of yore and also finds mention in the epic Ramayana as Kusha, named after the son of Lord Rama. However, its main claim to fame is its deep Buddhist roots. The town is home to several ancient stupas and viharas, dating to 3rd to 5th centuries. Most of these monuments were commissioned by the Mauryan Emperor Ashoka. Prior to its rediscovery in the 19th century, Kushinagar remained in a state of ruins mainly due to the violent invasions it endured over the period. Most of the sights and attractions in Kushinagar are associated with Lord Buddha. Most of these sites mark the last days of Buddha. The Nirvana Stupa was unearthed in 1876. Being a major Buddhist pilgrimage destination, Kushinagar attracts devotees from across the globe, many of whom have set base here to study and research about the Buddhist faith. Apart from the Buddhist landmarks, Kushinagar also houses the famous Sun Temple which was originally built during the Gupta period. The ideal time to visit Kushinagar is between November and March.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kushinagar being a place of major Buddhist attractions offers several 2 to 3 star standard and budget hotels. All these hotels offer good restaurants and accommodation facilities. Another option which one can look for is dharamshalas which are usually cheap and provide good basic services.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport is the Lucknow airport which is about 252 kms away. Some flights land at Kasia airstrip which is 5 kms away and Gorakhpur airport, about 46 kms away.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Padrauna, which is the city&rsquo;s head quarter, is linked with meter gauge railway line from Gorakhpur. The nearest railway stations are Gorakhpur and Deoria which are well connected to major Indian cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Kushinagar is well connected by road. National highway 28 is the nearest connecting highway to the city of Kushinagar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Regular road transport facilities of UPSRTC buses, local buses, autos and taxis are available from Gorakhpur to reach Kushinagar and vice versa.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - YAMA CAFE, IN KUSHINAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR COFFEE, NOODLES AND SANDWICHES)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(678, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'LAKHIMPUR KHERI', 'woman-978343_6402.jpg', 'woman-978343_6403.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Widely known as the Sugar Bowl of India, Lakhimpur Kheri is situated along the border with Nepal in Lakhimpur Kheri district of the state of Uttar Pradesh. The city is immensely famous for Dudhwa National Park which is the only National Park in the entire state. There are various species of wildlife animals and birds that can be seen here along with abundant natural resources and lush green vegetation. Lakhimpur Kheri travel guide is incomplete without a mention of its historical heritage. The city is well known for its sugar cane industry and supplies a massive part of the country&rsquo;s total consumable sugar to the different states. There is a large number of sugar mills situated here.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Lakhimpur Kheri has a lot for medium to budget accommodation options. Some of the comfortable hotels include Hotel Ashirwad, Hotel Pratham, Hotel Saluja and Hotel Surabhi.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest International Airport is Chaudhary Charan Singh International Airport, Lucknow, roughly two and half hour drive from Lakhimpur Kheri.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Lakhimpur Kheri has its own Railway Station named as Lakhimpur Kheri Railway Station. It is well connected to major cities like Bareilly, Delhi, Barauni, Amritsar, Lucknow, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Lakhimpur is at 124 kms distance from Lucknow and can be reached here by UPSRTC bus services.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - DHANPAL MISTHAN BHANDAR, AT&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;NATIONAL HIGHWAY 24 MAIGALANJ - (FAMOUS FOR GULAB JAMUN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - LAWAZA, NEAR NEARVRAJAPUR POLICE CHOWAKI, L.R.P.ROAD, MAHARAJ NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR NON VEGETARIAN DISHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(679, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'LALITPUR', 'color-208243_640.jpg', 'color-208243_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Widely known for its rich heritage, peace and tranquil beauty, Lalitpur is located in the state of Uttar Pradesh and is resplendent with religious and historical monuments. It is the district headquarters of Lalitpur district. Lalitpur travel guide is incomplete without a mention of the exquisite experience that the city can give to its tourists. Lalitpur represents a distinctive and enduring appeal to the viewers with its magnificent memento of the splendid past and present. One can see a clear picture of its culture from the remnants of the big monuments and magnificent dams and temples. It is a part of Jhansi division. Widely known for its rich heritage, peace and tranquil beauty, Lalitpur is located in the state of Uttar Pradesh and is resplendent with religious and historical monuments. It is the district headquarters of Lalitpur district. Lalitpur travel guide is incomplete without a mention of the exquisite experience that the city can give to its tourists. Lalitpur represents a distinctive and enduring appeal to the viewers with its magnificent memento of the splendid past and present. One can see a clear picture of its culture from the remnants of the big monuments and magnificent dams and temples. It is a part of Jhansi division. Lalitpur district is one of the districts of Uttar Pradesh state of India. Lalitpur district is a part of Jhansi division. Lalitpur is the main town and administrative headquarters. The district occupies an area of 5039 sq kms.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Lalitpur has some medium to budget accommodation options. There are medium to budget hotels in the city with all facilities to make the stay a memorable one.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest Domestic Airport is the Gwalior Airport from the city, roughly four hour drive from Lalitpur. It is well connected with the cities like Delhi and Mumbai via Air India flight.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - Lalitpur has its own Railway Station named as Lalitpur Railway Station which is connected to all the major cities of Madhya Pradesh and Uttar Pradesh with other cities like Nagpur, Kanpur and Lucknow.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road </strong>- Lalitpur is well connected through Madhya Pradesh and Uttar Pradesh State Road Transport Corporation (MPSRTC) and (UPSRTC).<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">1 - ANAND BHOJNALAY, AT&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;TALABPURA ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR PARATHA AND DAL THADAKA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(680, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'MAHOBA', 'crimson-rose-301449_12802.jpg', 'crimson-rose-301449_12803.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">A small district in Uttar Pradesh Mahoba is famous for its glorious history. Located in the Bundelkhand region, Mahoba shares close cultural roots with Khajuraho, known for its erotic caves and sculptures created during the Chandela rule. It was the capital of the Chandel Rajputs, who ruled the Bundelkhand region from the 10th to the 16th centuries. The word Mahoba is derived from Mahotsav Nagar or the city of great festivals. Mahoba is home to several interesting monuments, buildings and religious sites. The Shiv Temple dominates the landscape around the Gukhar Mountains and contains the idol of the Lord in the Tandav position. The Kakramath temple, located on an island in the Madan Sagar Lake also attracts its share of devotees. Rahila Sagar Sun Temple is a 9th century shrine is located in the western side of Rahila Sagar. Also visit Chandika Devi temple and Gokhar Parvat which houses shrines dedicated to Hindu, Jain and Buddhist religion. November to February is the best time to visit when the weather is mild and pleasant.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">The city of Mahoba is well equipped with good staying options which include luxurious hotels to economy and deluxe hotels, lodges and budget accommodations.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest airport is Khajuraho Airport which is about 55 kms away. The Satna airport is also about 131 kms away.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Train</strong> - The Mahoba Khajuraho line was inaugurated in the year 2008. Several trains from major cities such as Delhi and Mumbai pass through the town.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Mahoba is well connected by National Highway 76 which connects the city to the other villages and towns in the district such as Supa, Kulpahad and others.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(681, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'MEERUT', 'me6.jpg', 'me61.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The city of Meerut in Uttar Pradesh is the 63rd fastest growing urban areas in the world and the 14th fastest developing city in India. The city is also one of the major army cantonments in north India and is a hub for several industrial activities. It is one of the largest producers of sports goods and musical instruments in the country and the largest producers of bicycle rickshaw in the world. According to a recent report U.S. financial services firm Morgan Stanley, titled Alpha Wise City Vibrancy Index: A Guide to India&rsquo;s Urbanization Meerut is ahead of Delhi and Mumbai in terms of vibrancy. Like the rest of India, Meerut too is benefitting from the economic book in the country a fact that is evidence in the number of real estate projects including shopping complexes, malls, roads, flyovers and apartments that are coming up in the city. Like any other city in India, Meerut too is home to several temples and religious sites such as Chanda Devi Temple and Mansa Devi Temple that attract hordes of devotees, especially during Navratris. The Jama Masjid caters to the Muslim population while the Jain community finds peace at the Shri Shantinath Digamber Jain Temple. The St John Church and Sardhana church serve the Christian community while the Bale Miyan ki Dargah and Shahpeer Sahab ki Dargah attract devotees from all walks of life who come here to get their wishes fulfilled. The Ecological Park and the Pine Children&rsquo;s Park provide the much needed green spaces and solace from the chaos of the city. Appu Ghar is a popular amusement park for children. The Shahid Smarak pays tribute to the soldiers who lost their lives during the freedom struggle. December to February is the ideal time to visit Meerut.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are a number of hotels in Meerut of different categories to suit the need and demand for accommodation. To meet the need and demand, there are a number of hotels and resorts who cater to diverse interests of the people coming from worldwide. One can find hotel accommodation of every category and type to suit the need of present day. Bookings for most of the hotels here can be done online or on phone, and credit-debit cards are accepted in almost all of them.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport is Delhi but the city has an airstrip which is used by government officials.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Meerut has four railway stations that are served by trains from Delhi and other cities in India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Meerut has well developed road transport with the neighbouring cities of Delhi, Ghaziabad, Haridwar, etc. NH 24, NH 58, NH 119, NH 235, pass through the city of Meerut. The Delhi Meerut 14 lane Highway is an ambitious plan undertaken by the respective government that aims to reduce the travel distance between the two cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - Buses, tempos, rickshaws and taxis, are the prominent modes of transport within the city and to the neighbouring towns. Intermittent bus stops at 18 locations, excellent bus service to every part of the city makes bus commutation the most reliable mode of transport. One can also find rickshaws, shared jeep, tempos that have a license to ply up to 16 kilometres from the city limits.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - JAIN, LOCATED AT 5 KILOMETERS FROM MODINAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR SHIKANJI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - DEV FOODS, AT NEW MARKET, BEGUM BRIDGE ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR CHAAT ITEMS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - MANCHOW, AT&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;ABU LANE, MERUT CANTT - (FAMOUS FOR CRISPY VEG HAKKANOODLES AND VEG BULLETS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - BIGGIES, AT&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;NH-58, MEERUT BYPASS ROAD, JALOTI - (FAMOUS FOR BURGERS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - SINGH FRESH, AT NH 119, SOTIGANJ - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - BRAJ MOHAN STALL, NEAR RV COLLEGE - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;PANIPURI, BURGERS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - VIPIN STALL, AT BUDHANA GATE - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORI, SAMOSA AND JALEBIS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - HARIYA, AT ABU LANE - [FAMOUS FOR BUTTERMILK (LASSAI)]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>9 - GUPTA, AT BUDHANA GATE - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;SANDWICHES AND TEA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>10 - PINKI, AT CIVIL LINES POLICE STATION ROAD, LALKURTI BAZAAR - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;CHOLE BHATURE AND GULAB JAMUN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(682, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'MIRZAPUR', 'lake-277600_640.jpg', 'lake-277600_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Mirzapur is one of the districts of Uttar Pradesh with the Mirzapur town as the district headquarters. The main attractions of Mirzapur are its several ghats and historical structures that date to the British era in India. While signs of civilization date to 5000 BC, Mirzapur was actually established by the British East India Company in 1735. There is ample evidence in the form of painted rocks and other artefacts that show that Palaeolithic age existed here in the Belan River Valley region. Some interesting petro glyphs found in the sandstone of the Vindhya Range are more than 17000 BC. It is little wonder then that the district attracts historians and archaeologists and also a fair share of visitors who apart from delving into the history also come here to appreciate the scenic ghats which are beautifully lit up with diyas and lights, especially during the religious festivities. Mirzapur is also known for its carpet and brassware industries. Its historical significance and Palaeolithic Age roots apart, Mirzapur is famous for its scenic beauty. Some of the popular ghats include Pakka Ghat and Nar ghat. The best time to visit Mirzapur is from November to April when the temperature is mild and pleasant. The main business in Mirzapur is carpet manufacturing. In the Vindhya region of Mirzapur city, there are cement industries. Limestone deposits are also found in this city. Cotton is the most common agricultural crop grown in the rural areas of Mirzapur city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Accommodations are available at Hotels of UPSTDC. One can also stay at dharamshalas and guest houses readily available at any time.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Nearest airport is Varanasi located at a distance of 60 kms. There are many domestic flights from Varanasi to other major airport towns in India. Daily flights are available to and from major cities of India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail</strong> - Mirzapur Station has direct rail link to all major cities of India. Both taxis and auto rickshaws are available at station to commute easily.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - National Highway 7 and State Highways 5 and 5A are the nearest highway connecting Mirzapur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Mirzapur is well connected to the rest of the country with good motor able roads. There are frequent state owned (UPSRTC) bus services available from Mirzapur to major parts of the state.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - CHHAPPAN BHOG, AT BARAUDHA - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - ASHOKA SWEET HOUSE, AT RAMAIPATTI - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;CHENE KA RASGULLA)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(683, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'MUZAFFARNAGAR', 'road-272844_640.jpg', 'road-272844_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Located in Uttar Pradesh, Muzaffarnagar is known for its temples and other places of religious interest. The city was established during the Mughal period by a Sayyid Jagirdar and christened in honour of his father, Muzaffar Ali Khan. Strategically located on the highway connecting Delhi to Dehra Dun the town is fast growing into a major city close on the heels of Noida. The earliest evidence of settlement in this region goes back to the times of the Harappan Civilisation. It also finds mention in Mahabharata and according to local legend, the epic war was fought in the fields of the present village of Pachenda and the army camps of both sides were located at sites which are now famous as Kaurawali and Pandavli. In fact, Muzaffarnagar is located close to Hastinapur and Kurukshetra, both places closely associated with the Great War epic. The town regained prominence during the Mughal rule when Sayyid Jagirdar established the town and named it after his father. A bustling city today, Muzafarnagar is giving a stiff competition to Noida and Meerut and is emerging as a major hub for investment in the real estate and other industries. It is also well known for its Bhairo Temple that attracts millions of devotees especially during the festive period. As said above, the main attraction of the town is Bhairo ka mandir. While here the devotees also take time out to visit other temples and religious sites such as Ganeshdham, Durga Dham, Hanuman dham and Kali Nadi Mandir. Vahelna, a scenic village near Muzaffarnagar, is home to Shri 1008 Parshvnath Digamber Jain Atishye Chetra commonly known as Vahelna Jain Mandir. It is a major historical and pilgrimage centre in north India. Muzaffarnagar enjoys mild and pleasant climate from November to April and, so this is the best time to visit the city. However, the religious sites and temples attract visitors the year round.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Also being an industrial town, Muzaffarnagar attracts a lot of business officials to promote industries in this area. To cater all this footfalls, the district has quite a number of good and well groomed hotels and guest houses in reasonable budget. The best part of these hotels is that they all have separate features which help traveller to choose according to their own preference.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest airport is Jolly airport in Dehra Dun. From Dehra Dun, tourists can hire a taxi or take a public/private transport bus to reach Muzzafarnagar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- The railway station in Muzaffarnagar is visited by regular trains from cities such as Delhi, Jalandhar, Amritsar, Allahabad, Dehradun, Haridwar, and Mumbai.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Muzaffarnagar is located on the highway that runs from Delhi to Dehra Dun. State transport buses connect it to major cities like Allahabad, Meerut, Haridwar, Ujjain and Delhi.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - CHEETAL GRAND, LOCATED AT KHATAULI BYPASS, NH 58 - (FAMOUS FOR OMELETTE AND &nbsp;SANDWICHES)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - NANDI SWEETS, LOCATED AT OLD GUR MANDI ROAD, NEAR RAMLEELA GROUND - (FAMOUS FOR KAZU KI BARFI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - JAIN CHAAT CORNER, LOCATED AT MATA WALA MANDIR RD, GHER KHATTI, NEW MANDI - (FAMOUS FOR ALOO TIKKI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - HAVELI @ KHATAULI, LOCATED IN MUZAFFARNAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR PANEER PAKORA AND EGG NOODLES&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - 7 ELEVEN FOOD COURT, LOCATED AT &nbsp;DWARIKA PURI - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;SAMOSA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n6 - MADANLAL, LOCATED AT BHOPA RD, CIVIL LINES SOUTH - (FAMOUS FOR BUTTERMILK AND RASGULLA)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(684, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'NOIDA', 'yamuna-expressway-385360_640.jpg', 'yamuna-expressway-385360_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Noida is actually an acronym for New Okhla Industrial Development Authority and is managed by the authority with the same name. It came into being on 17 April 1976 and every year this day is celebrated as Noida Day. Noida is situated in the Gautam Buddh Nagar district of Uttar Pradesh and its administrative headquarters are in the nearby town of Greater Noida. Along with Gurgaon, Noida is the centre of the booming IT industry in India and today almost all multinational companies have their offices here. Some of the noted names include IBM, Miracle, Fujitsu, AON Hewitt, Ebix, CSC, Tribal Fusion, Fiserv, TCS, WIPRO, HCL, Ericsson, Tech Mahindra, Adobe, and DELL. Most companies have chosen Noida as their headquarters because of the Special Economic Zone status that it enjoys. Noida&rsquo;s proximity to New Delhi is another factor. In fact, the head office of the Software Technology Park, formed by the Government of India to promote the IT industry. Noida has witnessed an exponential rise in the real estate industry over the recent years. Several prestigious projects have come including the Worlds of Wonder, being developed jointly the M/s International Recreation Parks Pvt. Ltd and Unitech Limited. The Great Indian Place is one the biggest malls in north India which houses all major brands from across the globe. Besides, there are several recreational centres and multiplexes also found here.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Hotels ranging from reasonable to expensive are all available in the city. Tourists can look around several options for hotels or guest houses in this city which best suits the pocket and convenience.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The closest airport is in New Delhi from where one can take a taxi to Noida which will cost around Rs. 900. Alternatively, tourists can also take Airport Metro line till New Delhi and then take Metro to Noida via Rajiv Chowk.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Noida lies on the National Highway 27 and Noida expressway which makes it very easily reachable and there is great interconnectivity of roads around the city as well.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- The closest railway station is the Hazrat Nizamuddin railway station, New Delhi from where one can take a taxi or an auto for about Rs. 200. Or can simply get down at New Delhi railway station which has great metro connectivity.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- Noida has very convenient connectivity inside the city. Tourists can opt for cycle rickshaws, buses, taxis, auto rickshaws or the best of all the Metro, which is cheap and one does not have the tension of getting stuck in the traffic. Metro can be used to travel towards locations that are a bit far. However, Metro doesn&#39;t have sector wise connectivity so one can opt for buses. Please note that autos and taxis could be expensive options for travelling.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - REENA RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT DHARMA MARKET, BEHIND SAB MALL, SECTOR 27 - (FAMOUS FOR BUTTER CHICKEN)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - LAKSHMI COFFEE HOUSE, LOCATED AT &nbsp;BRAHMAPUTRA SHOPPING COMPLEX, CAPTAIN VIJYANT THAPAR MARG, SECTOR 29 - (FAMOUS FOR DOSA, UTHAPAM AND IDLI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - PUNJABI BY NATURE, LOCATED AT P-19, SECTOR 18 (ATTA MARKET) - (FAMOUS FOR MAKKI KI ROTI WITH SARSON KA SAAG)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - TEASTA TEA SHOP, LOCATED AT SHOP NO 16, ARUN VIHAR, SECTOR 37 - (FAMOUS FOR SANDWICHES, COFFEE AND BUTTER COOKIES)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n5 - COLONEL&#39;S KABABZ, LOCATED AT J 56, SECTOR 18 - (FAMOUS FOR ALOO PARANTHA WITH DAL MAKHNI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n6 - FRESH FOOD FACTORY, LOCATED AT E 1, BLOCK E, SECTOR 3 - (FAMOUS FOR PAV BHAJI, GULAB JAMUN AND GAZAR KA HALWA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - ROLLS KING, LOCATED AT J 03, NEAR GIP FOOTOVER BRIDGE, SECTOR 18 - (FAMOUS FOR PANEER ROLLS TO CHICKEN TIKKA ROLLS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n8 - BRAHMAPUTRA MARKET, LOCATED AT MAHARISHI DAYANAND MARG, SECTOR 29 - (FAMOUS FOR BHEL PURI, VEG AND NON-VEG KABAB, KESAR PISTA KULFI, DAHI PURI, ALOO TIKKI, MOMOS, SPRING ROLL, MILKSHAKES, CHICKEN BIRYANI AND DOSA)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>9 - HUNGRY I, LOCATED AT A-BLOCK MARKET, NEAR AMITY SCHOOL, SECTOR 44 - (FAMOUS FOR PASTA, NOODLES, PIZZA, VEG AND NON-VEG SNACKS, SALADS AND BEVERAGES)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n10 - GOLI VADA PAV NO. 1, LOCATED AT KRISHNA APRA PLAZA, PLOT 3, BLOCK P, SECTOR 18 - (FAMOUS FOR ALOO TIKKI, MAKAI PALAK AND VADA PAV)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n11 - BISTRO 37, LOCATED AT SHOP NO. 11, GODAVARI COMPLEX, ARUN VIHAR, SECTOR 37 - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;BURGERS AND HOAGIE IS A TYPE OF SANDWICH FILLED WITH &nbsp;MEATS, CHEESES, VEGETABLES, AND OTHER CONDIMENTS)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(687, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'ORAI', 'AAA8.jpg', 'AAA9.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Orai is a city and a municipal board in Jalaun district in the Indian state of Uttar Pradesh. It is the district headquarters for Jalaun district which is part of Jhansi division. It is situated on NH 25 in between Jhansi and Kanpur and on Bilrayan Panwari SH 21. It is located in the Bundelkhand region. Orai has been named after a saint Uddalak because he worshipped there and has historical value because of its location, which is between Jhansi, Mahoba and Kalpi. Orai was also known as the city of King Mahil who was infamous for his bad habits and back biting; he betrayed his nephews Aalah and Udal and one of them, Udal, was killed and according to a proverb Aalah is still alive because he is immortal. Jalaun was the scene of much violence during the Revolt of 1857. In the later 19th century, the district suffered much from the invasive Kans grass, owing to the spread of which many villages were abandoned and their land thrown out of cultivation.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Orai offers with a range of accommodations from Dharamshalas, low to medium ranged hotels to luxury hotels.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air</strong> - Nearest airport is Lucknow Amausi Airport which is at a distance of about 166 kms from Orai.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Train</strong> - Regular trains from Orai Railway Station show well connectivity of Orai with the rest of the country. &nbsp;One can choose from a wide variety of trains to get to and from the city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Road</strong> - Orai, located midway between the cities of Kanpur and Jhansi, lies on National Highway 25 which is soon going to be a part of east of the National Highway Corridor Project. One could add charm to their journey ahead by watching beautiful sunrise from this National Highway.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Orai is located about 40 kms away from the nearest bus stop Mauranipur Bus Stand. One can drive down or avail the services of local and UPSRTC bus services to move to Orai from the nearby and major cities.</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(688, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'PILIBHIT', 'highway-115457_640.jpg', 'highway-115457_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Pilibhit, also known as Bansuri Nagari the land of flutes, is a municipal board in the Pilibhit district of Uttar Pradesh. It is the north eastern most city of Bareilly division which is situated in Rohilkhand region of the sub Himalayan belt on the boundary of Nepal. Pilibhit is surrounded by the city Udhamsingh Nagar and the territory of Nepal, on the south by Shahjahanpur district, on the east, the city is flanked for a short distance by city Kheri and the remaining distance by the Shahjahanpur and on the west the district of Bareilly. A scenic town in Uttar Pradesh Pilibhit is one of the richest forest areas in the state. The town has very high tourism potential however the 54 kms long border with Nepal poses some grave security issues. Pilibhit is home to some interesting ancient historical monuments that throw light on the culture and tradition of the region. There are also some beautiful pilgrimage destinations set amidst beautiful natural settings. Pilibhit is home to the Pilibhit Tiger Reserve where you can spot the majestic animal. Other natural attractions include Gomat Taal, Devha-Ghagra Sangum and Raja Venu Ka Tila. There is also a beach here by the name of Chuka Beach in the Mahof forest range. The sunset from the beach is a mesmerizing sight. There are several temples and religious sites located in Pilibhit including the Gauri Shankar Temple which is around 450 years old. Old Pilibhit, whose existence can be traced to the 15th century, is very colourful and bustling with people and energy. Like other cities in north India, Pilibhit also enjoys summer, monsoon and winter.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Tourism in Pilibhit has always been a major activity in the city because of its historical, religious and popular tourist spots. As a result the businesses of hotels and guest houses have become quite healthy in the last few years. Few of the finest lodging places are present in Pilibhit with almost all necessary facilities. Though there are no 5 star or 4 star hotels in Pilibhit but there are few budget hotels in the area which are extremely good to stay and absolutely light on the pocket. These budget hotels are ideally value against money.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Nearest airports to Pilibhit are at Lucknow and Delhi. One can avail the facility of both local and prepaid taxies and UPSRTC buses to reach Pilibhit city from Lucknow airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Trains are the most comfortable mode of travel that one can opt for while visiting Pilibhit. Trains from Pilibhit runs to Agra, Lucknow and also to places like Nainital in Uttarakhand. Trains from New Delhi are taken till the city of Bareilly, and from there one can either opt for buses or local meter gauge trains to reach Pilibhit.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Pilibhit is well connected by road. National highway 74 and State highways 26 and 29 are the nearest connecting highways to the city of Pilibhit. Once you enter the city, you can take benefits of local buses, autos and taxi services to move within the city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - One can drive down or avail the services of local and UPSRTC bus services to move to Pilibhit from the nearby and major cities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - VAISHALI RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT TULARAM, PILIBHIT - (FAMOUS FOR DAL MAKHANI AND CHOLE BHATURE)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - ETAH SWEETS, LOCATED AT SH 29, TULARAM, PILIBHIT - (FAMOUS FOR KACHORI AND KALAKAND IS A DESERT MADE FROM MILK, PANEER OR CHHANA AND SUGAR)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '');
