(689, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'RAE BARELI', 'eggplant-253196_640.jpg', 'eggplant-253196_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The district of Rae Bareli in Uttar Pradesh is named after its head quarter town. The district was carved out in the year 1858 by the British. The district has several attractions to its credit including the Samaspur Bird Sanctuary and the Indira Gandhi Memorial Botanical Garden. In fact, Rae Bareli is closely associated with the Gandhi family and had been their strong hold till as recent as in 2012, it was the first time that the Congress party was humbled in this constituency. There are several things to see and do in Rae Bareli. As mentioned above, one of the greatest attractions of the district is the Samaspur Bird Sanctuary which is home to more than 250 species of birds and other animals. The Indira Gandhi Memorial Botanical Gardennot only houses medicinal, herbal and decorative plants but also a research institute. The historical town of Dalmau also has several attractions to its credit including the King Dal&#39;s fort, Bara Math, and Mahesh Giri Math. The best time to visit Rai Bareli is from November to March when the weather is mild and pleasant.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Rahi Tourist Bungalow is a top rated hotel in Raebareli. It offers world class amenities at a very reasonable price. This 2 star hotel in Raebareli is situated at the city centre and is easily approachable from all the important places of the city. Other than Rahi Tourist Bungalow there are many quality hotels to stay in Raebareli. Most of these are located at the epicentre and are easy to commute from any point in the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Rai Bareli does not have any airport. Tourists can take a flight to New Delhi or Lucknow and from there tourists can take a bus or train to Rai Bareli.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- There is a major railway station in the city of Rae Bareli that is visited by trains from Lucknow, Allahabad, Varanasi, Dehradun, Delhi, Bareilly, Pratapgarh, Ramnagar and Kanpur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Buses to the city of Rae Bareli are available from major cities in Uttar Pradesh, including Lucknow, Allahabad, Meerut, Jhansi and Bareilly.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SUYASH RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT NATIONAL HIGHWAY 330A, OPP. PRAGATIPURAM COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR KULFI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - BATOHI, LOCATED AT KUTCHERY RD, NIRALA NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;GULAB JAMUN AND KAJU BARFI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - DINESH RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT SH36, HABIBULLA NAGAR, RATAPUR - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSAS WITH CHUTNEY)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n4- SOMU DA DHABA, LOCATED AT NH 24B, RATAPUR - (FAMOUS FOR MATAR MUSHROOM CURRY AND PANEER TIKKA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(690, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'RAMPUR', 'calf-207977_640.jpg', 'calf-207977_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">City of Rampur is located in Moradabad region of Uttar Pradesh. It is surrounded by district Udham Singh Nagar in North, Bareilly in East, and Moradabad in West and Badaun in South. Spread in area of 2367 sq kms Rampur is 192 mts above sea level. Nawab Ali Muhammad Khan, the adopted son and successor of Sardar Daud Khan, chief of the Rohillas in Northern India was the Founder of Rampur. In 1737, he received the territory known as Kather from Emperor Muhammad Shah but unfortunately in the year 1746, he lost virtually everything in a contest with the Nawab Wazir of Oudh in 1746. In the medieval age Rampur was under the administration of the rulers of Delhi. &nbsp;It was once famous for fine arts and music. The main industries of Rampur are wine making, sugar processing, weaving textiles and manufacturing agricultural implements. The culture of Rampur shows the great impact of arts, literature and culture, laid down by the Nawabs of Rampur. One can see a vast collection of Oriental manuscripts and beautiful miniature Mughal paintings in Rampur Raza Library, housed in a former palace. Rampuri cuisine which forms a part of the Mughal cuisine tradition was also developed by the chefs of the Nawabs. The Rampur Greyhound, considered as a test of courage, was the favoured hound of the Nawabs for jackal control. It was also used to hunt lions, tigers, leopards, and panthers.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Rampur offers with a wide range of accommodations from low to medium budget hotels to luxury hotels. Luxury hotels tariff is usually high. These hotels offer various facilities like internet facility, laundry, doctor on call, television etc. Many hotels also have a car rental desk, where cars can be rented by tourists to go around the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Nearest airport to Rampur is located at New Delhi which is at a distance of about 206 kms. Another alternative is the Amausi Airport at Lucknow which takes about 5 and half hours.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Rampur railhead is well connected with regular trains with the rest of the country. One can choose from a wide variety of trains to get to Rampur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - National Highways 24 and 87 and State highway 25 are the nearest connecting highways to the city. Situated on the National Highway 24, the state capital is 302 kms in east and national capital is 185 kms in west.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - One can drive down or avail the services of local and UPSRTC bus services to move to Rampur from the nearby and major cities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - VIA DILLI RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT NEAR AXIS BANK, SHAUKAT ALI ROAD, CIVIL LINES - (FAMOUS FOR BUTTER CHICKEN)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - CHICKEN KING, LOCATED AT RAH-E-RAZA, OPPOSITE GREENWOOD SCHOOL, CIVIL LINES - (FAMOUS FOR KEBABS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(691, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'SAHARANPUR', 'rice-194781_640.jpg', 'rice-194781_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The town of Saharanpur is located in a district by the same name in the state of Uttar Pradesh. The town is a prominent tourist destination and is famous for its cottage industries including wood carving. It is also famous for its agricultural produce such as mangos and basmati rice. The town boasts a rich history and has over the years witnessed the rise and fall of several empires all of which have left an indelible mark on its fabric. People flock to Saharanpur to see the age old temples including Shakumbhari Devi temple and Bala Sundari temple of Deoband. The Naugaja Peer is much favoured by the devotees who come here to get their wishes fulfilled. Apart from the temples, Saharanpur also has several colonial buildings that have stood the test of time. The Botanical Gardens, established by the British East India Company in the city are also quite famous and serve as a centre for botanical research. The ideal time to visit Sarahanpur is between November and April.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Saharanpur has some deluxe and medium to budget accommodation options. Royal Residency is a deluxe accommodation option with all high class facilities which makes your stay a reliable and memorable one. The medium and budget accommodation includes hotels near Railway Station.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport is Jolly Airport in Dehra Dun. From Dehra Dun, tourists can take a bus or hire a taxi to reach Saharanpur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Saharanpur has a major railway station and is served by trains such as Kanpur, Jammu Tawi, Howrah, Amritsar, Ujjain Chennai, Dehradun, and Haridwar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Saharanpur is well connected by road to other cities of the state as the NH 73 and SH 57 as well as SH 59 runs through the city. Both the state highways are being converted into four lanes and the work is in progress.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - For local transport, UPSRTC buses, cycle rickshaws, auto rickshaws, taxis and private buses are available.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - KHUSHI FAST FOOD, LOCATED AT GILL COLONY - (FAMOUS FOR PASTA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - KATHI JUNCTION, LOCATED AT 2A/792/2, RAILWAY ROAD - {FAMOUS FOR KATHI ROLL IS A TYPE OF SANDWICH MADE FROM MUTTON (LAMB) PIECES AND BREAD}<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - SNACK POINT, LOCATED AT SHOP NO. 1, MISSION COMPOUND - (FAMOUS FOR MOMOS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - GURU NANAK DHABA, LOCATED AT NH 73, SUBHASH NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR LACCHA PARATHA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n5 - RAJ HANS, LOCATED AT BHAGAT SINGH RD, OPPOSITE TO BANK OF INDIA - (FAMOUS FOR MILKSHAKES)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(692, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'SRAVASTI (SHRAVASTI)', 'statue-1283327_640.jpg', 'statue-1283327_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Sravasti in Uttar Pradesh was one of the six largest cities in India during the times of Gautam Buddha. The city finds mention in the epic Mahabharata and is believed to have been named after the legendary king Shravasta. However, Buddhist legend has it that it took its name from sage Savattha who lived there. Sravasti is a major pilgrimage centre for the Buddhists and attracts devotees not only from India but from other parts of the Buddhist world including Sri Lanka, Japan, China, and Thailand. The Jetavana Monastery is where Buddha spent the maximum years during his stay in Sravasti. His first visit in the city was on the invitation of Anathapindika, whom he had met in Rajagaha. The Anathapindika is believed to have been built by him. Located on the back of the river Rapti, Maheth is encompassed by a high earthen rampart with a brick wall with several gates and four high bastions. Excavations carried out in this region have unearthed the ruins at Saheth which include plinths and foundations of numerous Buddhist structures including stupas, monasteries and temples. Balrampur district is a famous tourist destination in the area and is famous for rich literary landscape. Located on the banks of the Rapti River, Sravasti was the capital of the kingdom of Kosala and was ruled by the king Pasenadi who was a disciple of Buddha. It is believed that the Enlightened One passed the greater part of his monastic life here. Several monasteries were built here including the Jetavana and the Pubbarama, and the monastery of Rajakarama, built by Pasenadi. Today, the city walls of Savatthi are still standing, encompassing the remains of three ancient buildings: Anathapindika&#39;s stupa, Angulimala&#39;s stupa, and an ancient temple dedicated to a Jain Tirthankara. Outside the city gates, there is another stupa were the Twin Miracle took place. Sravasti is of great significance to the Jain community, and it is believed that Sambhavnath, the third Jaina Tirthankara was born here. Like other cities in north India, the ideal time to visit Sravasti is from November to April when the weather is pleasant and mild. However, Sravasti is a major pilgrimage destination for the Buddhists and Jains and invites visitors the year round.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Plenty of budget range hotels are available to stay in Sravasti. Tourists Bungalows are available to stay in Sravasti. These are maintained by PWD.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest airport is the Lucknow Airport that receives flights from cities such as Delhi, Mumbai, Chennai, Agra, and Bangalore. From here, one can take a taxi or the state transport bus to reach Sravasti.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Train</strong> - There are two options to reach Sravasti by rail. One is from Balrampur, which has a small station which is served by several trains. The second and the convenient option is the station at Gonda that is connected to major cities such as Delhi, Lucknow, Ahmadabad, Bangalore, Kolkata and Agra.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Bus</strong> - The city is served by private carriers and state transport buses from major cities in the state including Lucknow, Varanasi and Sarnath.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>By Road</strong> - The city has good roadways which includes NH 730 and SH 1A. The NH 730 runs through the centre of the city and it connects itself with SH 1A at the Katra locality of Sravasti.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(693, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'SITAPUR', 'country-boat-254366_640.jpg', 'country-boat-254366_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Located in Uttar Pradesh, Sitapur is the district headquarters of Sitapur district and is located in Lucknow division. It is one of the most historically relevant districts of the state. The district is believed to have been founded after Goddess Sita, wife of Lord Rama. Sitapur Travel guide is incomplete without a mention of its historical heritage. The district is among one of the five religious places where the Hindus travel in their Panch Dham Yatra visit. Here, Purans were written by Rishi Ved Vyas, the writer of Indian epic, Mahabharata. Then it was known as Naimisharanya. Another place Misrikh, near Naimisharanya celebrates its holy importance due to the conviction that Maharshi Dadhichi contributed his bones to Devtas for making Vajras.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are a lot for deluxe and medium to budget accommodation options nearby Sitapur. There are some deluxe hotels and medium to budget accommodations available with all facilities which make the stay a reliable and memorable one.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest International Airport is Chaudhary Charan Singh International Airport, Lucknow, roughly two hour drive from Sitapur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Sitapur has its own Railway Station named as Sitapur Railway Station. It is well connected to major cities like Bareilly, Delhi, Barauni, Amritsar, Darbhanga, Ambala, Gonda, Shahjehanpur and Lucknow.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - National highway 24 passes from Sitapur. Sitapur is 89 kms away from the capital Lucknow.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - MISRIKH RASOI AND GUPTA SWEETS, LOCATED AT LALBAGH, NAI BASTI - (FAMOUS FOR AALOO TIKKI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - MAHESH SWEET &amp; RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT CAPTAIN MANOJ PANDEY CHOWK, CHUNGI CHOWKI - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSAS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - HARDAYAL SWEETS, LOCATED AT CHHOTILINE RAILWAY STATION - (FAMOUS FOR PATTIES)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(694, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'SONBHADRA', 'farmer-207954_640.jpg', 'farmer-207954_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Sonbhadra is the second largest district in the state of Uttar Pradesh. Located in the south eastern range of the Vindhya Mountains, it is served by the Sone River which flows from east to west. Sonbhadra tourism has immense historic and cultural significance and is home to several ancient monuments, forts and buildings. Several interesting monuments and buildings serve as important tourist places in Sonbhadra. The Vijaygarh Fort located in the Sonbhadra district dates back to the 5th century. It was built by the Kol Kings and is widely known for its exquisite rock carvings, inscriptions and cave paintings. Then there is the Naugarh Fort, which was built by the Kashi Kings. Although it now serves as a guest house for Government dignitaries, the small fort is still considered a prominent tourist attraction. The Agori Fort is another iconic fort which lies surrounded by three rivers on three sides. Sonbhadra is also home to the Salkhan Fossil Park. The park is of great geographic and historical significance. The fossils here date back to the Proterozoic period which means that they are more than 1400 million years old. The district of Sonbhadra is known for its several Cave painting sites found in the Vindhya region. The Lakhania caves are located in the Kaimur ranges and are known for their beautiful ageless rock paintings. These historic paintings are about 4000 years old and bring to life the culture and belief of an era gone by. In terms of religious sites, the Shiv Dwar is a famous temple dedicated to Lord Shiva and Goddess Parvati. The best time to visit Sonbhadra is between November and March.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The second largest district in Uttar Pradesh i.e. Sonbhadra has good hotels in its grounds which also offer tasty food service.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport is the Mayurpur airport. This is a private airport and is used by chartered and private planes. The nearest public airport is the Varanasi International airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- The nearest railway station is Mirzapur railway station though Robertsganj railway station and Chopan railway station are also within convenient distance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Sonbhadra is about 90 kms from Varanasi. A metalled road passes through the city. It is well connected by road to major cities of Uttar Pradesh. The highway connecting Varanasi and Waidhan passes through Sonbhadra.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport </strong>- The district has numerous local transportation services like car, bus, auto, taxi, tempo etc to support the huge population of the state. Car hire agencies are huge in number in Sonbhadra.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SINGH MISTHAN, LOCATED AT CHOPAN ROAD, IN FRONT OF GURDWARA, OBRA - {FAMOUS FOR VEGETARIAN CUISINE AND GAJAR KA HALWA ( DESSERT MADE FROM CARROT)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - MUNNA, LOCATED AT SECTOR V, NTPC COLONY, SHAKTI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR PANIPURI AND ALOO TIKIYA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - BIHAR MISTHAN BHANDAR, LOCATED AT &nbsp;NH 75, RENUKOOT &nbsp;- (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;SWEETS AND KACHORI)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(695, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'SULTANPUR', 'barley-1117282_640.jpg', 'barley-1117282_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">A historical city known for its tradition and culture, Sultanpur is situated on the banks of River Gomti. It is located in the state of Uttar Pradesh and is the headquarters of Sultanpur district. The city is famous for its unique tradition and culture and was previously known as Kushapura. Sultanpur is an industrial district. Also, there are large number of crops cultivated in the district like rice, wheat, barley, sugarcane and poppy. Jagdishpur is the main industrial centre in Sultanpur. The existence of the city of Sultanpur dates back to the period of Lord Rama. It is considered that Lord Rama divided the city among his brothers and sons. The old city lay on the bank of River Gomti and was known as Kusapura or Kusabhavanpur, named after the founder of the city, Kusa. Sultanpur is distinguished for its unique culture. Originally known as Kushbhawanpura it was renamed as Sultanpur, which means, city of beautiful vines. The city came under the Muslim rule in the 12th century. Although the area has been part of successive North Indian kingdoms through centuries, the recorded history of the city began in the colonial times. Long a centre of Hindu and Buddhist culture it fell under Muslim occupation in the 12th century. The town was completely destroyed during the military operations of the Revolt of 1857.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Sultanpur has a lot for medium to budget accommodation options. &nbsp;Some of the comfortable hotels include Hotel Vijai Deluxe, Mohini Guest House, Raj Hotel, Hotel Pushpanjali, Gaurav Guest House and Garden View Guest House. The hotels are homely and laced with the modern amenities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest Domestic Airport is Bamrauli Airport, Allahabad, roughly two hour drive from Sultanpur. It is well connected to New Delhi through Air India. The second nearest International Airport is Chaudhary Charan Singh Airport, Lucknow, roughly 148 kms from Sultanpur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- It has its own Railway Station named as Sultanpur Railway Junction which is connected to the all major cities of Uttar Pradesh and other state like Lucknow, Kanpur, Delhi, Jaipur and Bhopal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Sultanpur is well connected by road to other cities of the state of Uttar Pradesh and other states. UPSRTC buses and private buses operate here.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - AVANTIKA RESTAURANT,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT FAIZABAD - SULTANPUR RD, CIVIL LINE - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;KAJU BARFI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - SPICY FOOD COURT, LOCATED AT NO.51, MAIN MARKET, MEHRAULI GURGAON ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR CORN SOUP)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - PRATAP DHABA, LOCATED IN SULTANPUR - (FAMOUS FOR SHAHI PANEER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - COOL CORNER, LOCATED AT NEXT TO STATE BANK OF INDIA, NEAR BUS STAND, CIVIL LINES - (FAMOUS FOR MASALA COLD DRINKS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - PRAKASH, LOCATED AT CIVIL LINE - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA AND PANIPURI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - BHOLE, LOCATED AT SHASTRI NAGAR- {FAMOUS FOR BUTTERMILK(LASSI)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - NEW BHOLA, LOCATED AT CIVIL LINES - (FAMOUS FOR VEG KABAB PARATHA)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(696, 14, 31, 755, 'Uttar Pradesh', 'INDIA', 'UNNAO', 'ox-plough-253419_640.jpg', 'ox-plough-253419_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Unnao is a city of Uttar Pradesh state in northern India. Unnao city is the district head quarters and it is a part of Lucknow Division. North side of this city is bounded by city Hardoi, south side is bounded by city Raebareli, east side is bounded by Lucknow and the west side is bounded by River Ganga which separates it from Kanpur &amp; Fatehpur. Unnao city is a part of Central Ganges Plain of the state covering an area of 4558 sq kms. About 1200 years ago, the city was covered with extensive forests. Later in the 3rd quarter of the 12th century, Godo Singh who was a Chauhan Rajput cleared the forests and founded a town called Sawai Godo. Shortly afterwards this place was passed into the hands of Kannauj rulers, who appointed Khande Singh as the Governor of the place. Unwant Singh, a Bisen Rajput and a Lieutenant of the Governor, killed Khande Singh and built a fort there and renamed this place as Unnao. The city is mainly drained by the river Ganga and its tributaries Kalyani, Khar, Loni and Marahai in the western part of the district and by Sai River in the eastern part of the city. Unnao is also very popular for its samosaas prepared exclusively in shop situated in the premises of Unnao Railway Station. Unnao, being a small city, does not have big Malls or super markets for shopping. The people of this city usually go to their main local market, Sadar Bazaar for shopping.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Unnao proffers with low to medium range hotels and dharamshalas. One can choose from these options according to their budget.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Nearest airport is at Amausi, Lucknow which is at a distance of about 30 kms from Unnao. Lucknow is connected by air to all major cities of the country.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The nearest railway station is at Kusumbhi which at a distance of 2 kms from the main city. The Kusumbhi railhead is well connected with regular trains with the rest of the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Unnao is well connected by road. National highway 25 and State highway 58 are the nearest connecting highways to the city of Unnao.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - One can drive down or avail the services of local and UPSRTC bus services to reach Unnao from the nearby and major cities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - SURUCHI, LOCATED AT NEAR RAILWAY STATION - (FAMOUS FOR EGG ROLLS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - AWASTHI SWEETS, LOCATED AT KANPUR - LUCKNOW RD, GANDHI NAGAR - (FAMOUS FOR GULAB JAMUN AND RASSGUALLA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - MANORANJAN, LOCATED AT KACHODI GALI, NEAR RAILWAY STATION - (FAMOUS FOR PAV BAJI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '9'),
(697, 17, 50, 1898, 'Rio di la Plata 	', 'Argentina', 'BUENOS AIRES', 'boca-juniors-1712628_640.jpg', 'boca-juniors-1712628_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Argentina&rsquo;s capital, long considered the Paris of South America, has a rich history in its own right. From popular attractions to known gems, there are a million and one sights to see in this metropolis. Elegant yet always bustling, Buenos Aires symbolizes the very essence of Argentina. South America&#39;s second largest city, Buenos Aires is the political, economic, and cultural capital of Argentina as well as gateway to the rest of the nation. Its compact centre is replica of Paris with many charming corners where tidy high rise apartments are there with attractive 19th century buildings. Most first time visitors are surprised to find that the big city has managed to preserve its old traditions. This energetic port is the gateway to Argentina. Buenos Aires is often called the Paris of South America for its classic architecture and rich European heritage. The city has boulevards and alleys, cafes and markets. The city is a patchwork of neighbourhoods that cover over 202 sq kms and has a population of about three million.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Buenos Aires has seen a boom in boutique properties spring up in recent years, so pick the barrio that bests suits the needs and let hoteliers do the rest. The city&rsquo;s old world elegance and modern spirit come together in top rated accommodations across town. Options run between luxury five star treatment down to more budget boutique hotels in up and coming barrios.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Buenos Aires international airport, Ezeiza International Airport connects Argentina to most major cities in North America, Europe, Asia and Australasia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - There are four main train stations in Buenos Aires Retiro, Constitution, Once and Federico Lacroze. Long distance domestic trains, and trains to neighbouring countries of Uruguay and Brazil can be boarded from any of these stations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Buenos Aires is connected very well to the rest of the country and some neighbouring countries as well through a strong bus network. Retiro bus station is the main terminal from where you can catch buses to virtually any place in the country, including the popular districts of Catamarca, Cordova, The Pampa, Mendoza, Santa Cruz, Santa Fe, Tucuman and more. Buses also serve the neighbouring countries of Bolivia, Brazil, Chile, Peru, Uruguay and Paraguay. Over 100 Argentinian bus companies operate out of this terminal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - The best way to get around Buenos Aires is by subway, also known as &quot;the subte.&quot; The subte is quick, affordable, and easy to navigate with maps, easily attainable at subte stations. Bus lines are also efficient, although they are less trotted by tourists. Taxis are another convenient way to get around the city, look for black and yellow radio taxis, which are metered. With an efficient public transportation system and abundance of taxis, there&#39;s no need to rent a car in Buenos Aires.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - BUENOS - [FAMOUS FOR CHIMICHURRI IS A GREEN SALAD MADE FROM CHOPPED PARSELY, OREGANO, ONION, GARLIC, CHILLI PEPPER FLAKES, OLIVE OIL GARLIC, CHILLI PEPPER FLAKES ; CHORIPAN IS ATYPE OF SANDWICH MADE WITH CRUSTY BREAD (MARRAQUETA OR BAGUETTE), CHORIZO ; &nbsp;EMPANADA IS A STUFFED BREAD CONISTS OF MEAT, CHEESE ; ALFAJOR IS ASWEET MADE FROM FLOUR, HONEY ALMONDS AND HAZELNUTS ; ASADO IS ATRADITIONAL DISH ; CHORIZO IS A SPICY SAUSAGE MADE FROM PORK ; LORCO MADE FROM WHITE CORN, BEEF OR PORK, AND OTHER OTHER VEGETABLES ; HUMITA IS A DISH MADE FROM &nbsp;CORN, &nbsp;MILK, ONION, SPICES AND SOME AND GOAT CHEESE ;&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - EL PARRILLON, NEAR THE LOLA MORA FOUNTAIN, AVENDIA DE LOS ITALIANOS, COSTANERA SUR - [FAMOUS FOR CHIMICHURRI]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - EL COCACOLERO, ACROSS THE STREET FROM THE AEROPARQUE, COSTANERA NORTE - [FAMOUS FOR SANDWICHES]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(700, 17, 50, 1897, 'Rio Negro', 'Argentina', 'BARILOCHE', 'lakes-322703_1280.jpg', 'lakes-322703_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Located in the foothills of the Andes in the northern Patagonia region of Argentina, San Carlos de Bariloche, or Bariloche for short, is one of the most beautiful destinations in the country. Surrounded by a number of lakes and found within the Nahuel Huapi National Park, this tourist hotspot offers excellent opportunities for skiing, trekking and mountaineering. Situated at the shore of Lago Nahuel Huapi, in the heart of the National Park with the same name, Bariloche has one of the most beautiful landscapes imaginable. Its location as well as the vast number of summer and winter activities, which it offers in its surroundings, has helped the city to become an unforgettable pearl of Patagonia. Trekking, skiing, snow activities, golf, mountaineering, sailing, canopy, rafting, kayaking, fishing and horse riding are only some examples of possible outdoor activities in Bariloche. Bariloche offers travellers thrilling outdoors activities as well as a pretty Swiss style town full of chocolate shops and boutiques. Bariloche The city of Andean Lakes a city so distinctly alpine that it could easily be mistaken for a Swiss town somewhere in the Alps, what with its rolling green slopes, its snow capped mountain tops, its quaint Swiss style architecture, and even its chocolate shops.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">As a major tourist destination, Bariloche has a long string of hotels, many of which are fairly affordable. The trick is to make reservations months in advance, especially if visiting during the high seasons. There are options of budget hotels, mid range hotels and luxury holels which offer cheap beds and are the most luxurious hotels in the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The San Carlos de Bariloche International Airport receives flights from Buenos Aires, El Calafate, Mar del Plata, Mendoza, and Cordoba daily so going into the city by plane is the best alternative, especially if book tickets in advance to get them for cheaper.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - There is only one train, operated by the Tren Patagonico Company, coming into Bariloche every week and it&rsquo;s from Viedma, a city that&rsquo;s all the way on the opposite side of the region.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - From Buenos Aires, it takes from 17 to 22 hours to drive to Bariloche. Tourists can drive less than 15 hours to the city of Neuguen, stay there for the night, and then continue on to Bariloche the next day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Buses to Bariloche take about 19-22 hours from Buenos Aires and about 6-8 hours from Chile. There are several bus companies that provide this service, including Via Bariloche and El Crucero del Norte. These companies have different bus types with different seating options, serve meals and drinks to their passengers, and takes all the way to the city&rsquo;s Terminal de Omnibus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around </strong>- Getting around the city is also quite easy. Once in the city centre, it&rsquo;s best to go around on foot to explore the shops and buildings there. Outside the city centre is another story. If want to see the city&rsquo;s main attractions, which include the beaches, ski areas, and lakes of the Nahuel Huapi National Park, have to take public transportation, going on bus tours, or rent a car. In fact, while the city&rsquo;s bus system is reliable and cheap, most visitors in Baraloche rent cars it&rsquo;s faster and more efficient.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - ALMAZEN DE SABORES, AT LOS RADALES, DINA HUPAI, RIO NEGRO, ARGENTINA - [FAMOUS FOR RED CURRY STEAK AND BRAISED PATAGONIAN PORK AND VEG CURRY STEAK AND BRAISED PATAGONIAN PORK AND VEGETABLE BRUSCHETTA]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - LA TRATTORIA DELLA FAMIGLIA BIANCHI&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;ESPANA, AT SPANA 590, SAN CARLOS DE BARILOCHE, ARGENTINA - [FAMOUS FOR RISOTTO, PASTA AND SEAFOOD]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - LA SALAMANDRA PULPERIA, Av., EXEQUIEL BUSTILLO 5818, SAN CARLOS DE BARILOCHE, ARGENTINA - [FAMOUS FOR EMPANDAS]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - HOLLY RESTOBAR, AT AVENIDA JUAN M. DE ROSAS 435, SAN CARLOS DE BARILOCHE, ARGENTINA - [FAMOUS FOR PIZZAS AND &nbsp;SEAFOOD]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - BUTTERFLY, AT HUA HUAM 7831, SAN CARLOS DE BARILOCHE - [FAMOUS FOR GAZPACHO AND FONDUE]</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(701, 17, 50, 268, 'Mendoza', 'Argentina', 'MENDOZA', 'mendoza-936227_1280.jpg', 'mendoza-936227_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\nWith jaw dropping scenery, abundance of exotic wildlife, colonial towns and cities rife with superb cuisine and vibrant culture, it is no wonder that Argentina is a popular travel destination. Located in the southern region of South America in a large, elongated shape, Argentina was sparsely inhabited by a few indigenous tribes before Spain&rsquo;s colonized it in the 16th and 17th centuries. Today, the country is an independent republic featuring varied landscapes from rich plains to thick jungle, majestic mountains, pastoral steppes and impressive glaciers.Mendoza, the wine capital of Argentina, is situated in the scenic foothills of the Andes. In 2009, National Geographic named Mendoza one of the top 50 places to visit in the world. Even for non oenophiles, it&rsquo;s a convenient base for exploring the province&rsquo;s rugged countryside. Famed for its neat vineyards and thriving wine production, Mendoza remains the place to visit for a pleasant combination of relaxation and recreation. Though many tourists spend the bulk of their Mendoza holiday touring the renowned Argentine wine route, the city and the surrounding area offer a range of other activities, from paragliding and parachuting to hiking and boating. Equally suitable for adrenaline addicts in need of constant excitement and hedonists on the lookout for self indulgence, a trip to Mendoza also places near the Aconcagua, the tallest peak in both the Western and Southern Hemispheres. Located in the western region of Argentina, Mendoza is one of the most popular tourist destinations in the country.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Mendoza is a very liveable city, and many choose to stay for a few weeks to take language courses and the like, there are a number of short term apartment rental companies, concentrated in downtown. East of the centre is the more low rent area, and contains the cheaper hostels. Check out the unique magical places to stay in, with a range that covers authentic rustic, to modern lodging, and delivers a true Mendoza experience.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Gov. Francisco Gabrielli International Airport serves Mendoza, with flights to and from Buenos Aires taking less than 2 hours and less than 1 hour to and from Santiago.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- A new 12.6 kilometre light rail line, the Metrotranvia Mendoza, opened for regular service in October 2012 and serves five areas of the Greater Mendoza conurbation. The line runs from Estacion Central at the site of the former intercity passenger train station, near the city centre south to Maipu.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - The large bus terminal is about two kilometres from the city center. There are daily bus connections to all major destinations including Bariloche and Santiago de Chile, a beautiful 7 hour bus ride crossing the Andes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Local Transport</strong> - The public transport system includes buses, the Mendoza trolley bus system, and taxis. The trolley buses are more comfortable than the diesel buses, but are slower, not as numerous nor is the system as extensive. Buses are cheap and plentiful, but a little confusing at first. Taxis are plentiful, metered and fairly cheap, costing about the same as in Buenos Aires.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - MENDOZA - [FAMOUS FOR PARCELS IS CARNE IS ABAKED OR FRIED PASTRY (MINCED OR CHOPPED BEEF OFTEN MIXED WITH ONION AND CUMIN) ; DULCE DE LECHE IS A SWEET MADE FROM MILK AND SUGAR ; TORTITAS &nbsp;ARE MADE WITH WATER, FLOUR, BUTTER, YEAST AND SALT, THREE TYPES OF TORTITAS ARE Pinchada, Manteca AND HOJA ; TOMATICAN IS LIKE A TOMATO SOUP MADE OF TOMATOES, EGGS, ONION, OREGANO BREADCRUMBS AND SALT ; HUMITA MADE WITH SWEET CORN, ONIONS, MILK, BUTTER AND CHILI FLAKES</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(702, 16, 51, 1896, 'New Providence', 'Bahamas', 'NASSAU', 'bahamas-783799_6402.jpg', 'bahamas-783799_6403.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Nassau, capital city of The Bahamas, lying on New Providence Island, the neighbour of Paradise Island, is both captivatingly old and new. This island pair maintains a distinct blend of international 21st century glamour, old world charm and tropical ease, giving holiday makers the freedom to do everything or simply relax and do nothing at all on their visit to Nassau &amp; Paradise Island. Travel to Nassau, the capital of the Bahamas and the island nation&#39;s largest city, for a lively taste of urban life. The city is full of bustling energy and makes for a high voltage day trip for cruise ship passengers touring the area. A visit to Nassau is the antidote to a sleepy day spent on the beach there is simply so much to do, from shopping at the numerous duty free shops on Bay Street, to exploring the city&#39;s historic Old Town, to throwing back drinks at one of the city&#39;s many bars. Its 685 acres of pure euphoria, developed almost exclusively to delight and accommodate visitors. The island boasts resorts, hotels, restaurants, shops, nightlife, a golf course, an aquarium and a casino.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Bungalows tucked into a tropical landscape, chic villas so close to the ocean one can taste the salt water, branded 4 star boutique hotels and quaint Bahamian vacation rentals that welcome guests like long time friends into their homes.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\n<strong>By Air </strong>- Lynden Pindling International Airport (formerly Nassau International Airport) is located 16 kilometres from Nassau. New Providence Airport on Paradise Island was closed in 1999 with runway removed and integrated into the resort on the island.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water </strong>- Ferries provide water travel around Nassau to the surrounding islands, namely Paradise Island. Prince George Wharf is the main port in the city that serves cruise ships with ports of call in Nassau. Transportation and shipping around the Family Islands is primarily through mailboats based at Potters Cay.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">By Road - Public jitney buses and taxis provide transport in and around Nassau. Rental cars are also available in the city and at the airport. The major road in Nassau is Bay Street for tourists. Bay Street runs the entire length of the Island from East to West.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - LUCIANOS OF CHICAGO&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;SITUATED ON EAST BAY STREET - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;SEAFOOD, PASTADISHES, FRIED CALAMARI(EGGS, BLACK PEPPER, TOMATO,LEMON JUICE) CONCH CAKES(TABOSCO SAUSE, EGGS, HUNGARIAN PAPRIKA AND PEANUT OIL)]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - POOP DECK, LOCATED AT EAST BAY STREET - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;BECKY&lsquo;S GRILLED CONCH(CONCH, ONION, TOMATO, SWEET PEPPER) BEEF TIP KEBAB(ANGUS BEEF, MUSHROOMS, ONION, SWEET PEPPER AND CHERRY TOMATOES)]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - CAFE MATISSE, LOCATED AT BANK LANE - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;FRITTO MISTO DI PESCE(FRY MIX SEAFOOD SPICY TOMATO AND LIME AVOCADO SAUSE) CARRE D&rsquo;AGNELLO( LAMB, MINT CRUST, POTATO GRATIN AND TOMATO)SCIALATIELLI CON FAVE, PANCETTA E PECORINO(FAVA BEANS, APPLEWOOD BACON AND PECORINO CHESSE)]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - LUKKA KAIRI RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT WOODES RODGERS WALK - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;CHICKEN PATTIE AND COCONUT CHESSECAKE]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - THE BEARDED CLAM SPORTS BAR AND RESTAURANT, LOCATED IN NASSAU - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;MACHO NACHOS(MADE FROM BEEF SALSA, JALAPENOS AND SOUR CREAM) CITRUS LIME CHICKEN TACOS(TOMATO, ONION AND CORN SALSA) FIRE CRACKER SHRIMP SLIDERS ROLLED IN GARLIC CHILLI SAUCE WITH LETTUCE AND MOZZARELLA)]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - ATHENA CAFE AND BAR, LOCATED IN NASSAU - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;YALANDJI( A APPETIZER FILLING OF RICE TOMATO, RED PEPPER, ONION MINT AND POMEGRANTE MOLASSES)]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - MONTAGU GARDENS, LOCATED AT EAST BAY STREET - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;CONCH FRITTERS(APPETIZER MADE FROM FLOUR, EGG, MILK, ONION AND BELL PEPPERS) CHICKEN SALAD SANDWICH( MEDELY OF CHICKEN &amp;FRESH HERBS ON A KAISER ROLL) GRILLED HOT DOG(AQLL BEEF HOT DOG ON ACRISPY FRENCH ROLL SNAPPER FILET(BAKED IN WHITE WINE AND CAPPERS]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - TWIN BROTHERS, LOCATED AT NASSAU - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;VARITIES OF JUICES, HOT COFFEE, FISH BURGER AND CURRY CHICKEN]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>9 - FAT TUESDAY BAR ANS RESTAURANT, SITUATED ON WEST BAY STREET - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;VEGGIE BURGER(MADE FROM TOMATO, ONIONS, LETTUCE AND PICKLES, CAPRESSE PANINI(FRESH MOZZARELLA CHESSE, TOMATOES, BASIL,GARLIC, AND BALSAMIC VINAIGREETE ON CIABATTA BREAD) CHICKEN FINGERS]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>10 - TWISTED LIME SPORTS BAR AND GRILL,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT WATERCOLOUR CAY - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;SWEET POTATO FRIES AND BURGERS]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>11 - BAHAMAS CRICKET CLUB, LOCATED ON WEST BAY STREET - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;OMELETTE, FRENCH TOAST(MADE FROM EGG, MILK AND BUTTER) AND BOIL FISH]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>12 - TAJ MAHAL, LOCATED &nbsp;AT PARLIAMENT STREET - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;SPICY MUSHROOM(COOK WITH ONIONS TOMATOES, GINGER, GARLIC, AND SERVE WITH NAN BREAD) SHISH KEBAB, &nbsp;CHICKEN TIKKA FISH PAKORA, POTATO BHAJI AND BEEF KORMA]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>13 - EAST VILLA RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT EAST BAY STREET - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;EGG ROLL AND CHINESE FOOD]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>14 - OLIVES MEZE GRILL, WEST BAY STREET - [FAMOUS FOR GYROS(PORK KEBAB), PANINI, PIZZA AND SEAFOOD]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>15 - NOBU, AT ROYAL TOWERS, ATLANTIS, PARADISE ISLAND - [FAMOUS FOR SASHIMI, TEMPURA, SOUPS, NOODLES, ROOLS]</strong></p>\r\n', '');
