(703, 16, 51, 1895, 'Grand Bahama', 'Bahamas', 'FREEPORT', 'desert-454648__340.jpg', 'desert-454648__3401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Freeport is the main city on Grand Bahama, an island in the northwest Bahamas off the Florida coast. It&#39;s best known for the oceanfront Lucaya district&#39;s beaches, resorts and shopping. Nearby, Deadman&#39;s Reef is popular for snorkeling, and the surrounding offshore waters have many dive sites. Up the coast, Lucayan National Park features extensive underwater caves plus kayaking and nature trails. Some islands in this region are known for their secluded beaches, some for their mega resorts, and others for their history and culture this one provides all three. And while Freeport offers great casinos and plenty of shopping, it still has more untouched natural land than other developed islands. So tourists can sip on a fruity rum drink, listen to some calypso or soca music, and put the feet in the sand. Freeport City is one of the gems of the Bahamas. Head here for fun water activities. From cruising waters to kayaking to the sea life, this is a great place to see nature.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The hotels are really expensive, and there are no cheap accommodations; it is better to book a hotel 4 or 5 star before travel or to rent a cabin on a cruise. Freeport has a wide variety of accommodations to cater to whatever the trip specifically needs from all inclusive resorts to hotels.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The main airport serving the city is the Grand Bahama International Airport, which receives domestic flights from various islands of the Bahamas as well as several international flights from the United States and Canada.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water</strong> - Freeport is also served by domestic Bahamian ferry services to other islands and by a regular international service to Fort Lauderdale, Florida, USA operated by Balearia Bahamas Express.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Freeport is located just 130 kms off the coast of Palm Beach, Florida.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - There are many forms of transportation available in Freeport. Taxis which are available at all the major tourist stops discuss a flat rate before the trip depending on how far to go and number of passengers. There are many tour bus services and taxis available to give a tour of the city of Freeport and highlight its features which may be more difficult on your own. Rental Cars is another option to see what Freeport has to offer.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - TONY MACARONI&#39;S CONCH EXPERIENCE, AT TAINO BEACH - [FAMOUS FOR ROAST LOBSTER AND SHRIMP]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - ROBINSON&#39;S SEAFOOD DELIGHT,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;AT CRUISE PORT - [FAMOUS FOR CONCH]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - CORAL REEF BEACH BAR, ON CORAL BEACH - [FAMOUS FOR BURGERS AND SANDWICHES]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - BECKY&#39;S RESTAURANT, AT SUNRISE HIGHWAY AT EAST BEACH DRIVE, MIDWAY BETWEENPORT LUCAYA AND DOWNTOWN FREEPORT - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;MINCED LOBOSTER, CURRIED MUTTON, FISH PLATTERS, BAKED OR CURRIED CHICKEN AND CONCH SALADS]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - CAFE BREEZE, IN PORT LUCAYA MARKETPLACE - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;COCONUT PANCAKES AND OMELETS]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - SABOR RESTAURANT AND BAR, LOCATED AT FREEPORT - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;BURGERS, CHEESE CAKE AND CHICKEN PAD THAI]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - PIER 1 BAHAMAS RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT LUCAYAN HARBOUR - [FAMOUS FOR SPAGHETTI ALLA PUTTANESCA(PASTA DISH MADE FROM TOMATOESOLIVEOILANCHOVIES CAPERS AND GARLIC) SANDWICHES, &nbsp;CHOCOLATE CAKE AND CHEESE CAKE]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - CAFE BREEZE, LOCATED AT FREEPORT - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;SCHNITZEL IS A MEAT MADE FROM MUTTON, CHICKEN AND VEAL) POTATO WEDGES(MADE FROM PARMESAN CHEESE, OLIVE OIL ONION POWDER, GARLIC POWDER]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>9 - ZORBAS, SITUATED AT PORT LUCAYA - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;MOUSSAKA(A POTATO BASE DISH) CARROTCAKE, AND CHICKEN KEBAB]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>10 - MARGARITAVILLA SAND BAR, LOCATED FREEPORT - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;VARITIES OF BURGERS AND SOFT DRINKS]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>11 - PEPPER POT, SITUATED AT EAST SUNRISE HIGHWAY - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;FRIED CHICKEN]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>12 - WENDYS, LOCATED &nbsp;AT PIONEERS WAY - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;BAKED POTATOES, BURGERS AND VARITIES OF SHAKES]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>13 - LIVITY VEGETARIAN TAKE-OUT AND JUICE BAR, LOCATED AT WEST ATLANTIC - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;VARITIES OF FRESH JUICES]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>14 - NEW LIFE NATURAL VEGETATION CELL FOOD, MARLBOROUGH BUILDING DOWNTOWN - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;MUSHROOM BURGER AND VEGGIE LASAGNA]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>15 - POLLO TROPICAL, LOCATED AT EAST SUNRISE HIGHWAY - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;ROSTED CHICKEN]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>16 - SILK CAFE,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT WEST ATLANTIC DR, FREEPORT - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;PANCAKES, BAKED CHICKEN AND VARITIES OF SOUPS]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(704, 16, 51, 1894, 'Eleuthra', 'Bahamas', 'ELEUTHERA', 'spanish-wells-363141_640.jpg', 'spanish-wells-363141_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Eleuthera is a 100 mile long wisp of land curving east like an archer&rsquo;s bow. According to literature, research and dependable local gossips, most people come here to relax. The beach bum is the true king here, his every do nothing need met by mile upon mile of obliging shores. These are the supermodels of the beach world pink sand, sunlight dancing on cerulean waters, sheltered coves, dramatic cliffs. Eleuthera offers a number of high-energy distractions. Wreck divers can explore the Devil&rsquo;s Backbone, fashionistas and foodies can salivate at the upscale boutiques and bistros of Harbour Island, and seasoned surfers can catch the waves of the eastern shore. While Harbour Island, a celebrity favorite, is developed and pricey though fabulous, mainland Eleuthera is ripe for off the beaten path exploration. The mangrove lined creeks of Winding Bay, on Eleuthera, provide quiet sanctuary for sea turtles of varying ages.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">On Eleuthera there are only about 3 hotels on the waterfront even though the island is 100 miles long. Many foreigners rent their homes. There is a residential Island resort development with spectacular ocean views, just a step away from our breath taking beach on the island of Eleuthera in the Bahamas.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Eleuthera has 3 airports North Eleuthera, Governors Harbour, and Rock Sound. All airports are small, open air and convenient. ELH and GHB have onsite bars and ELH has an onsite restaurant. ELH has the most flights arriving and departing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Boat</strong> - The ferry docks on Eleuthera at Governor&#39;s Harbour, Spanish Wells and neighboring Harbour Island. To get to and from Eleuthera and Harbour Island or Spanish Wells, tourists take a water taxi and a cab ride to reach the destination.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around </strong>- Eleuthera has no public transport system. There are taxis and car rentals. It&#39;s generally best to rent a car to explore Eleuthera. Hitchhiking is popular and locals are generally helpful and friendly. Bicycling is increasingly popular.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - SAMMY&#39;S PLACE, ROCK SOUND THE BAHAMAS - [FAMOUS FOR FISH BURGERS AND SANDWICHES, MARGARITA(IS A COCKTAIL MADE FROM TEQUILA AND LEMON JUICES)]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - DADDY JOE&#39;S RESTAURANT, LOCATED ON QUEEN&#39;S HIGHWAY - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;STUFFED CHICKEN BREAST, CHICKEN CURRY AND RICE, GUAVA DUFF( IS A DESERT MADE FROM GUAVA, FLOUR, EGG, BUTTER, SUGAR)]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - BUCCANNEER CLUB, LOCATED AT GOVERNER&#39;S HARBOUR - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;COCONUT RUM, CONCH BURGER(MADE FROM CONCH MEAT, SHRIMP, ONION ORANGES), CHOCALATE CAKE AND BAHAMIAN FOOD]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - MATE AND JENNY&#39;S PIZZA RESTAURANT AND BAR, LOCATED AT NORTH PALMETTO POINT - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;PEPPERONI(IS A VARIETY OF SALAMI MADE FROM &nbsp;PORK AND BEEF) AND PINEAPPLE PIZZA]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - DA PERK, SITUATED AT QUEEN&#39;S HIGHWAY AND GOVERNER HARBOUR - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;VARITIES OF COFFEE, PASTERIES AND SANDWICHES]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - SUGAR APPLE, IN THE BAHAMAS - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;BURGERS(CHICKEN AND BEEF), CONCH FRITTERSMADE FROM EGG MILK AND FLOUR WITH MIX OF PEPPER)]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - UNCA GENE&#39;S, LOCATED AT QUEEN&#39;S HIGHWAY, GREGORY TOWN - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;GROUPER FINGERS(MADE FRIM FISH), CONCH BURGERS]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - SANDBAR BEACH BAR AND GRILL, LOCATED AT VIVIAN PINDER ROAD MAIN STREET - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp; HAMBURGER]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>9 - LEE&#39;S CAFE, LOCATED AT GOVERNER&#39;S HARBOUR - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;BAKED CHICKEN AND CHICKEN CURRY, CHEESE MACARONI]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(705, 16, 51, 1893, 'Grand Bahama', 'Bahamas', 'GRAND BAHAMA', 'bahamas-1720653_640.jpg', 'bahamas-1720653_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Grand Bahama is the northernmost of the islands of the Bahamas, and the closest major island to the United States, lying 86 kilometres off of Palm Beach it is the fourth largest island in the Bahamas island chain of approximately 700 islands and 2400 cays. After years of playing second banana to bigger, more glamorous Nassau, Grand Bahama is finally coming into its own. If looking for a laid back, affordable getaway with a minimum of fuss, this is the place. The streets of Freeport, its main city, and Lucaya are clean and calm. Its golden beaches and aquamarine waters are rarely overcrowded, even in high season. All the amenities of a perfect vacation dive shops, restaurants, pubs, boutiques are at fingertips within a few block radius. No wonder Grand Bahama has become so popular with cruise ship tourists and families on quick weekend breaks. Outside the city, the 85 mile long island is an unexplored playground of mangrove swamps, sea caves and sandy cays. There&rsquo;s world class diving and snorkeling, great kayaking and bonefishing.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There&rsquo;s no shortage of luxury, allminclusive and self catered hotels to choose from in the Bahamas. Pick from high end resorts complete with butler service or self catered apartments to share with the family. The casinos and shopping malls of Downtown Nassau are a short stroll away too, so tourists are never far from entertainment.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Numerous Flights are available from South Florida. American eagle offers daily flights from Miami. Bahamasair, Continental Connection, and Spirit Airlines all offer daily flights from Fort Lauderdale. Delta Connection offers flights from Atlanta.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water</strong> - The ship is easy on budget and offers great onboard amenities. The Ship leaves Florida every other day which is great for travellers wishing to take a short two day vacation or a one day excursion. It drops passengers off in the mornings and then leaves back for Florida in the evenings.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around </strong>- Taxis are typically waiting for visitors at the airport and sea port. They are also easily summoned by phone. Public transport on the island consists mainly of minivans that ferry locals to and fro. It is a dollar to take the local bus line anywhere on the island. Taxis and Public Buses are clearly labled and are government regulated.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1- 3 - GRAND BAHAMA - {FAMOUS FOR SWITCHA(LEMONADE) IS A BEVERAGE MADE WITH NATIVE LIMES ; CONCH FRITTERS IS A SMALL BALLS OF DEEP FRIED BATTER MIXED WITH MINCED CONCH AND SERVED WITH SAUCE ; PATTYCAKES IS A FORM OF PANCAKES MADE WITH BANANA ; STEW FISH MADE WITH CELERY, ONIONS, TOMATOES AND VARIOUS SPICES}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2- TONY MACARONI&#39;S CONCH EXPERIENCE, LOCATED AT TAINO BEACH, GRAND BAHAMAS ISLAND - (FAMOUS FOR CONCH BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - BILLY JOE&#39;S, LOCATED AT &nbsp;LUCAYA, THE BAHAMAS - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;CHICKEN WINGS, FRIED CONCH, &nbsp;FRENCH FRIES AND CONCH SALAD, SWEET POTATO BREAD, FROZEN DRINKS (LIKE PINA &nbsp;COLODA)]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(706, 14, 52, 1892, 'Manama', 'BAHRAIN', 'MANAMA', 'bahrain-1744341_640.jpg', 'bahrain-1744341_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Manama has emerged as the capital of independent Bahrain after periods of domination by Portugal and Persians earlier in its history. Today, it is a modern capital with an economy based around the sales promotion industry as crude oil takes a less pronounced role in the economy. After periods ofPortuguese and Persian control and invasions from the ruling dynasties of Saudi Arabia and Oman, Bahrain established itself as an independent nation during the 19th century period of British hegemony. Although the current twin cities of Manama and Muharraq appear to have been founded simultaneously in the 1800s, Muharraq took prominence due to its defensive location and was thus the capital of Bahrain until 1921. Manama became the mercantile capital, and was the gateway to the main Bahrain Island. In the 20th century, Bahrain&#39;s oil wealth helped spur fast growth and in the 1990s a concerted diversification effort led to expansion in other industries and helped transform Manama into an important financial hub in the Middle East. Manama was designated as the capital of Arab culture for the year 2012 by the Arab League.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Naturally, there are a large number of excellent Manama hotels to choose from as well as a whole host of modern amenities such as shopping malls, bars and restaurants.While there are few budget hotels in Manama to choose from, those with plenty of cash to splash will be able to take their pick from a large number of four and five star Manama hotels, which can typically be found in places.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Bahrain International Airport is located on the nearby Muharraq Island, approximately 7 kms from the CBD. It is a premier hub airport in the Middle East. Strategically located in the Northern Persian Gulf between the major markets of Saudi Arabia and Iran, the airport has one of the widest range and highest frequency of regional services with connections to major international destinations in Europe, Asia, Africa, and North America.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Manama is the main hub of the country&#39;s road network. The widening of roads in the old districts of Manama and the development of a national network linking the capital to other settlements commenced as early as the arrival of the first car.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- Manama has a recently reformed comprehensive bus service that launched on 1 April 2015, with a fleet of 141 MAN buses. Regulated by the Ministry of Transportation, bus routes extend across Bahrain and around Manama.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around </strong>- Taxis are expensive, yet they are the only way to get around without renting a car. Renting a car is far more efficient economically. Altough bicycles are not popular, some hotel offer renting of them. There is no bicycle path in city, but cyclist ride on pavements, on way-sides etc.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - MANAMA,BAHRAIN - [FAMOUS FOR RHUA&rsquo;ASH IS A SWEET MADE OF (THREE- CORNERED PASTRIES FILLED WITH DATES, NUTS AND SULTANAS) ; ASALIA &nbsp;IS A SWEET PUFF PASTRY COVERED WITH HONEY ; BALALEET &nbsp;IS A DISH DISH PREPARED WITH NOODLES, SUGAR, CARDAMUM &amp; EGGS ; QAIMAT IS A SWEET DISH MADE FROM FRIED DOUGH FLOUR, ADDED WITH DATES SYRUP AND SESAMES ; BAYTH ELGITTA IS A FRIED COOKIE WITH A MIXTURE OF GROUND NUTS AND TOASTED IN POWDERED SUGAR ; GERS OGAILY IS A TRADITIONAL CAKE MADE WITH EGGS, FLOUR, SUGAR, CARDAMOM AND SAFFRON ; GHURAIBA IS A COOKIES MADE FROM FLOUR, BUTTER, POWDERED SUGAR AND CARDAMOM ; KHABEESA IS A SWEET DISH MADE FROM FLOUR AND OIL ; MACHBOOS IS A DISH MADE WITH MUTTON CHICKEN OR FISH &nbsp;; &nbsp;MAGLOOBA IS A &nbsp;RICE DISH COOKED WITH MEAT, POTATOES AND EGGPLANT ; QOUZI IS A DISH CONSISTING OF A ROSTED LAMB STUFFED WITH RICE, MEAT, EGGS AND OTHER INGREDIENTS ; LABAN IS A KIND OF SALTY BUTTERMILK ;QAHWAH IS THE NATIONAL BEVERAGE ; SOPA DE MANI IS A TYPE OF SOUP MADE FROM BEEF RIBS OR CHICKEN]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - CAFE LILOU, LOCATED IN MANAMA - (FAMOUS FOR RISOTTO IS A DISH MADE FROM RICE, BROTH, BUTTER AND ONION)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - JAN, LOCATED IN MANAMA - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN AND BEEF BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - NASEEF CAFE,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT GOVERRNMENT AVE. - [FAMOUS FOR SHAKSHOUKA &nbsp;IS A DISH MADE FROM EGGS POACHED IN A SAUCE , CHILLI PEPPER, ONIONS AND SPICED WITH CUMIN]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(710, 14, 52, 1892, 'Manama', 'BAHRAIN', 'MUHARRAQ', 'sunset-600767_640.jpg', 'sunset-600767_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Muharraq is Bahrain&#39;s third largest city and served as its capital until 1932 when it was replaced by Manama. The city is located on Muharraq Island and has long been a centre of religiosity. Adjacent to Muharraq are the man made Amwaj Islands, known for their large buildings, hotels and beaches. Muharraq is home to Muharraq Club, which is Bahrain&#39;s most successful football club. The city is also known for its traditional market and as a home of traditional arts and music Ali Bahar, a popular and successful Bahraini singer is from Muharraq. Muharraq&#39;s origins are ancient phoencian birthplace Tylos, its ancient name was Arwad. Just over the causeways from Bahrain Island, Muharraq Island could in many respects belong to a different country. With some beautiful old houses, a fort and a shore full of moored dhows and lobster pots, there&rsquo;s enough to keep visitors occupied in the atmospheric backstreets for at least half a day.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The third largest city of Bahrain, Al Muharraq is simply bursting with modern amenities such as a large selection of shops, restaurants as well as high quality hotels. Some of the best hotels in Al Muharraq are situated along Abdullah Avenue, which is conveniently close to local attractions such as the Bin Naser Moque and Shaikh Isa Bin Ali Mosque. However, Al Muharraq hotels can be found all over the city, especially along the avenue to Bahrain International Airport which is also on this island.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- This is the place where Bahrain International airport is located.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - From Manama tourists can easily get to Muharraq using one of the 3 modern causeways Sheikh Isa Bin Salma, Sheikh Hamad and Sheikh Khalifa Bin Salman. All of them will lead to the airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - There are many forms of transportation available in Freeport. Taxis which are available at all the major tourist stops discuss a flat rate before the trip depending on how far to go and number of passengers.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(711, 15, 53, 543, 'Alger', 'Algeria', 'ALGIERS', 'algiers-563687_640.jpg', 'algiers-563687_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Algiers is the capital city in Algeria and has an estimated population of around 3500000. The city was founded by the Ottomans and is rife with history and beautiful architecture. The ancient Casbah is a winding urban maze, with streets flowing through the old town like streams. Also worth exploring is the Dar Hassan Pacha, which was once the city&rsquo;s most decedent mansion. The interior of the house has been under renovation since 2005 and is unfortunately closed to the public. The city of Algiers offers visitors from the west a stark and beautiful contrast and an intriguing glimpse into the past, present and future of Algeria. Overlooking a scenic bay, the Mediterranean port city of Algiers enthralls visitors with its imposing skyline a blend of French colonial buildings, run down high rises, and white washed Islamic architecture nestled on the hillside. The crown jewel in the glimmering cityscape, the walled Kasbah reveals a labyrinth of narrow, sloping lanes flanked with old houses and mosques. As Algeria&#39;s capital and largest city, Algiers boasts modern amenities, quality restaurants, beaches, and a sweeping seaside promenade. On an Algiers vacation, tourists can delve into the country&#39;s rich history on a tour of the city&#39;s museums and notable buildings, or take scenic coastal drives and explore nearby beaches.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Lodgings in Algiers range from upscale chain hotels to affordable but basic backpacker accommodations. Mid market options consist mostly of modest, simple hotels catering to the business crowd. Hotels and resorts in Algiers concentrate mostly near the Kasbah and along the scenic waterfront esplanade.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Houari Boumediene Airport is located 20 kms southeast of Algiers the airport is named after former Algerian president Houari Boumediene. The terminal building is rather modern and relatively hassle free, comparable to airports in southern Europe. The airport is the home base of the flag carrier Air Algerie.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Algiers Central Train Station is located near the city centre. The station offers regular services to major Algerian cities such as Oran, Annaba, and Constantine. SNTF has made big improvements during the last years new air conditioned trains have been purchased and new routes launched.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Car </strong>- Being the capital of the country most, if not all major roadways in Algeria begin and end in Algiers. So getting into Algiers is quite easy. However, the infrastructure of Algerian roadways is not highly regarded so arriving by road might not be the most desirable option. There are a number of road projects around the country that are aimed at improving the infrastructure, most notably the Eastwest highway running from Annaba in the east to Oran in the west, of course coming through Algiers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - La Gare Routiere, Algiers&#39;s central bus terminus, located in the commune of Hussein Dey, offers a plethora of bus services to most major Algerian cities and towns. It is a very cheap and efficient way to get to and from a pair of Algerian cities. Most of the coaches used are modern and air conditioned so the rides are, more often than not, comfortable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Boat</strong> - There are regular ferry services to Algiers from Marseille, Nice, Palermo and Alicante.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - TAJ MAHAL BEN AKNOUN, AT 07 RUE LDIR TOUMI BEN AKNOUN ALGER - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;BIRYANI CHICKEN &amp; KARAHA CHICKEN)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - BAD BUNS, AT 6 CHEMIN SIDI YAHIA, HYDRA - (FAMOUS FOR BURGERS WITH DIFFERENT CHIPS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - TOUAREG, AT &nbsp;05, RUE MOHAMED DJEMAA KHEIDAR(CHEMIN MAKLEY - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;COUSCOUS IS A DISH MADE FROM SEMOLINA TOPPED WITH MEAT, VEGETABLES, AND VARIOUS SPICES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - MILK BAR, AT RUE LARBI BEN &nbsp;M&#39;HIDI - (FAMOUS FOR COFFEE, FRUIT JUICES AND PASTRIES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - SALAD BOX, AT BOULEVARD DU 11 DECEMBRE 1960, EL BIAR - [FAMOUS FOR CESAR SALAD MADE FROM LETTUCE, MOZZARELLA(CHEESE), BOILED EGGS, CUCUMBER, CROUTON]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - ALGIERS - [FAMOUS FOR CHAKCHOUKA IS A DISH OF EGGS POACHED IN A SAUCE OF TOMATOES, CHILI PEPPERS AND ONIONS OFTEN SPICED WITH CUMIN ; SAHALAB IS A BEVERAGE MADE FROM MILK, PISTACHIOS, CORNSTARCH AND COCONUT ; MECHOUI IS A ROASTED WHOLE LAMB, BANADURA SALATA B&#39;KIZBARA (TOMATO AND CORIANDER SALAD) ; LHAM LAHLOU (ALGERIAN LAMB AND DRIED FRUIT TAGINE)]</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(712, 15, 53, 554, 'Annaba', 'Algeria', 'ORAN', 'sunset-400858_640.jpg', 'sunset-400858_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Oran is the second city of Algeria it is a lively port city with heaps of character and beauty. Oran is an attraction in its own right and has historical buildings a plenty to explore including beautiful mosques, the Casbah and Le Theatre. The range of beautiful architecture is possibly the best of any city in Algeria. Oran is also a great place for scuba diving, sampling Algerian cuisine and listening to lively Rai music which has its origins in the city. Despite many positive reasons to visit the city there are also many signs of the country&rsquo;s political troubles in the 90s are visible in Oran. The city filled novelist Albert Camus with so much dread that he based his novel &lsquo;The Plague&rsquo; here. A cultural hub of Algeria, the coastal city of Oran boasts a long and varied history, from its founding by Moorish merchants in the 10th century, through centuries of Spanish, Ottoman, and French rule, and Algeria&#39;s bloody war for independence. Other things to do in Oran include browsing the stalls of the massive marketplace, exploring the nearby beaches, or dancing the night away at one of the numerous clubs and bars throughout the atmospheric port town. Algeria&#39;s second city is a lively port with plenty of history and a lot of rhythm. And it&#39;s this rhythm, more than any discernible sights that are the city&#39;s real attraction. Admire the imposing French colonial era architecture of the public buildings, watch giant containers being unloaded in the port and wander the hazy back lanes where young men kick footballs and washing flutters from little balconies.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Accommodations in Oran consist mostly of mid range hotels, with a couple of budget and upmarket options scattered around town. Affordable establishments offer basic facilities and clean, private rooms, while the more luxurious hotels, mainly clustered in the city center, include free Wi-Fi access and complimentary breakfast and often a scenic harbour view.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Oran Es Senia Airport while not as large as Algiers airport, it is still serviced by several international airlines.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Oran is at the western terminus of the Algerian rail network, there is a line continuing towards Morocco but it has been closed for decades due to political conflicts. Trains from the capital Algiers are plentiful however with several services daily.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Boat</strong> - One can also reach Oran by ferries from the ports of Marseilles, Sete, Alicante and Almeria, via the national company Algerie Ferries.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - ORAN - [FAMOUS FOR MAKROUDH &nbsp;IS A SWEET PASTRY FILLED WITH DATES, NUTS OR ALMOND PASTE ; MAHJOUBA IS A TYPE OF PANCAKE FILLED WITH TOMATOES AND ONIONS ; MATBUKHA IS A DISH MADE FROM TOMATOES, BELL PEPPERS, GARLIC, CHILI PEPPERS ; MROUZIA IS A SWEET AND SALTY TAJINE &nbsp;DISH MADE FROM BLEND OF SPICES WITH HONEY, CINNAMON AND ALMONDS ;&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - FRUITELLA, LOCATED AT BIR EL DJIR - (FAMOUS FOR FRUIT JUICES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - CARDINAL, LOCATED AT BIR EL DJIR - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;BURGERS)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(713, 15, 53, 544, 'Annaba', 'Algeria', 'ANNABA', 'turkey-995809_640.jpg', 'turkey-995809_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Annaba, informally known as Balad al-Unnab, is a city in the north eastern corner of Algeria near the Seybouse River, located in an eponymous province. With a population of 257359, it is the fourth largest city in Algeria. It is a leading industrial centre in eastern Algeria. Annaba is a coastal city and has undergone significant growth. Annaba has a metropolitan area with a higher population density than the other metropolises of the Algerian coastline such as Oran and the capital Algiers. Much of eastern and southern Algeria seeks the services, equipment, and infrastructure of the city. Economically, it is the centre for various dynamic activities, such as industry, transport, finance and tourism. Present day Annaba grew up on the site of Aphrodisium, the port of the Roman city. The modern town has since expanded south over Hippo&#39;s ruins as well. Its former names Bone and Bona derived from Ubbo, a local form of the name Hippo. Its informal name Balad al-Unnab town of the jujubes derives from that fruits abundance in the area. The vicinity of Annaba has yielded evidence of very early human occupation at Ain el Hanech, near Saida, including artefacts that show remarkable tool making craftsmanship. According to some sources, prehistoric Algeria was the site of the most advanced development of flake tool techniques in the Middle Early Stone Age.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Annaba is known for its beautiful beaches, hotels and nightlife. Most of the hotels are located in the center of Annaba, a city in the northeastern corner of Algeria near the river Seybouse and the Tunisian.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Annaba is best reached by air. Its airport, Rabah Bitat International Airport has regular services to Paris, Marseille, and Lyons. However, these frequencies aren&#39;t frequent and one should check an Air Algerie timetable when planning a trip. Annaba also has regular service to Oran.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Sea</strong> - There is a ferry service from Marseille to Annaba operated by, Ferries Algerie.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - One can also reach Annaba by road quite easily from most major Algerian cities. However, due to the lack of quality infrastructure this is the least desirable option.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - ANNABA - [FAMOUS FOR CHORBA IS A TYPE OF SOUP MADE FROM LAMB OR CHICKEN WITH VEGETABLES ; &nbsp;LHAM LAHLOU IS A DISH MADE FROM &nbsp;LAMB,CHICKEN OR BEEF AND SPICES (CINNAMON, TURMERIS, GINGER) OR DRIED FRUIT ; BOREK IS A BAKED PASTRIES MADE &nbsp;FROM &nbsp;PHYLLO PASSTRY, CHEESE, MEAT, EGG OR VEGETABLES ; BAGHRIR IS A TYPE OF PANCAKE MADE WITH SEMOLINA OR FLOUR ; &nbsp;THE GRITLIYA IS A DISH OF STEAMED AND DIPPEDIN A BROTH OF LAMB, CHICKPEAS AND MEATBALL ; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(714, 15, 53, 1891, 'Bejaia', 'Algeria', 'BEJAIA', 'rio-de-janeiro-768914_1280.jpg', 'rio-de-janeiro-768914_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Bejaia is situated on Algeria&rsquo;s Mediterranean coastline and this is the city&rsquo;s primary attraction for tourists. The history of the city is expansive and has been settled by the Vandals, Byzantines, Moroccans and Ottoman Turks. The museum in the city has various artifacts to prove this turbulent history. In addition to the museum there is also an impressive Spanish fortress and the so called Monkey Peak which is home to the endangered Barbary Macaque monkey. A Mediterranean port and provincial capital, Bejaia juxtaposes ancient monuments and national parks with the center of the Algerian and Western Mediterranean oil industry. Settled since antiquity, Bejaia has seen Byzantine administration, Muslim feudal rule, and French colonialism. Today, sightseeing in Bejaia reveals this endemic mix of cultures, influences, and imagery a true feast for history buffs.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Bejaia has both economical lodgings and luxurious hotels, as well as options in between, merging the best of both categories. During the summer season many residents rent out houses and cottages on the Mediterranean Sea to tourists. Other choices include shared and private rooms, as well as secluded beach resorts with catering service and spa facilities. Internet advertising is widely used here, but checks everything personally, or through a friend, to prevent fraud.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest major airport is Soummam Abane Ramdane Airport. This airport has international and domestic flights and is 10 kms from the center of Bejaia, Algeria.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The Algerian train company is named SNTF; tickets can be bought at the Train stations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Distance between Algiers and Bejaia is 182 kilometres in Algeria. Route starts from Bejaia and ends at Boumagueur.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(715, 15, 53, 560, 'Tlemcen', 'Algeria', 'TLEMCEN', 'tlemcen-1769739_640.jpg', 'tlemcen-1769739_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Tlemcen&nbsp;boasts a rich history and diverse culture, and is now a melting pot for various musical and artistic styles. The textiles and handicrafts here are beautiful examples of Berber and Arab Andalusian heritage, and the architecture is spectacular also, with the mosque standing as a stunning architectural masterpiece. It is also one of the oldest and best preserved Almoravid buildings in the whole of the country. Tlemcen is idyllic, framed by the majestic mountains and still enshrined in artisan charm. For stunning Moorish buildings in Algeria there is only one option Tlemcen. The buildings here can compete in beauty with those in Southern Spain or Morocco. The town was important for the Romans but sadly not much evidence has survived from those times. Sights include the Great Mosque, the Eiffel Bridge and waterfalls in the nearby National Park of Tlemcen. Tlemcen has its sights firmly set on the future and is currently in the process of building what will be the largest university campus in the country.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Tlemcen has both economical lodgings and luxurious hotels, as well as options in between, merging the best of both categories. Affordable establishments offer basic facilities and clean, private rooms, while the more luxurious hotels, mainly clustered in the city centre.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Tlemcen is served by the international Zenata Airport. Tlemcen is 12 miles from Zenata Airport</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Tourists can train to get from Algeria to Tlemcen. This journey costs $12 and takes 7 hours.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Boat</strong> - There is no direct crossing between Algiers and Tlemcen tourists will have to use another mean of transport to combine with ferry in order to complete the sea crossing Algiers Marseille.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - 1 - TLEMCEN - [FAMOUS FOR MECHOUI IS A DISH OF SHEEP OR A LAMB SPIT-ROASTED ; COUSCOUS IS A DISH of SMALL STEAMED BALLS OF SEMOLINA ; HARIRA IS A TYPE OF SOUP &nbsp;MADE FROM FLOUR, TOMATOES, LENTILS, CHICKPEAS, ONIONS, RICE AND MEAT OF (BEEF, LAMB OR CHICKEN) ; SHAKSHOUKA IS A DISH OF EGGS MIX WITH SAUCE, CHILLI PEPPERS, ONIONS, AND SPICED WITH CUMIN]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - L&#39;EQUINOXE, LOCATED AT N22 - (FAMOUS FOR TAGLIATELLE &nbsp;IS A TYPE OF PASTA MADE FROM FLOOR AND EGGS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - MARRAKECH, LOCATED IN TLEMCEN - [FAMOUS FOR TAJINE L&#39;HAMME (LAMB CHUNKS WITH CUMIN FLAVORED MEATBALLS)]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(716, 15, 54, 447, 'Littoral', 'Benin', 'COTONOU', 'funkyp-and-white-lady-1577898_640.jpg', 'funkyp-and-white-lady-1577898_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Cotonou is the largest city in Benin and the country&#39;s primary port of entry for visitors. The city is located on the country&#39;s coastline, in the south. &nbsp;It is situated along the Gulf of Guinea. Cotonou is Benin&#39;s capital in everything but name: a vibrant, bustling, full on city, and very much the economic engine of Benin. As a first port of call, it can be a little overwhelming, but life can be sweet in Cotonou, with good nightlife, great restaurants and excellent shopping ideal for end of trip souvenirs. It&#39;s also the most cosmopolitan and Western place in the country, which means a slightly higher level of creature comforts and a good place to stock up on essentials before venturing into rural areas of the country. In the Fon language, the word Cotonou means the mouth of the river of death. The area was settled as a fishing village during the time of the Dahomey Kingdom. The French were given permission to build a trading post, until they were given the region altogether in 1868. The city was used to defend against the British in their conquests. Cotonou grew to become the largest city in the country, right up to independence.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Hotels in Cotonou give a warm welcome, with comfortable rooms, friendly staff and a great atmosphere. There are 5 to 3 star hotels, lodges and budget hotel in the heart of the business district of Cotonou.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Cadjehoun Airport is located just west of city centre, and is the primary airport serving the city and the country. It has scheduled services from most African capitals, along with connections to Brussels and Paris. Short haul flights from nearby Lagos are a popular way of reaching Benin.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Buses from nearby capitals Accra, Lagos and Lome are plentiful. Amongst others, ABC Transport offers daily services. There are bus services from Cotonou to every city in the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - There is a train route that goes halfway up the country, from Cotonou to Parakou, run by L&rsquo;Organisation Commune Benin Niger des Chemins de Fer Et Transports. While the train takes longer than a bush taxi, it&#39;s a much more relaxing way of travelling. The trains usually stop at Bohicon, which is 4 hrs from Cotonou.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - The best way to get around is by taxi, although tourists have to go to a main gare to find them. A cheaper alternative is by moto, locally called zemidjans which means get me there fast in Fon. They are simply moped taxis which are very popular. Fares are negotiable, and there are no meters.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - LA CABANE DU PECHEUR, LOCATED AT FIDJROSSE PLAGE, ROUTE DU PECHEUR, FIYEGNON 2 - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN SALAD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - MAQUIS PILI PILI, AT CARRE 342 QUQRTIER ZONGO - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN AND LAMB DISH)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - TANDOORI NIGHTS, PISTE AMALCO - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN MALAI TIKKA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - LE REGAL VEGETAL, AT RUE 964, HAIE VIVE - (FAMOUS FOR PLAT DU JOUR IS A DISH MADE FROM FRESH WILD SALMON, POTATOES AND PEAS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - CI GUSTA, LOCATED AT RUE 449 - (FAMOUS FOR VARITIES OF ICECREAMS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - O&#39;GRILL, LOCATED AT A PROXIMITE DE LA SONAEC GANHI - (FAMOUS FOR GRILLEFD MEAT LIKE CHICKEN, PORK AND FISH)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - ROYAL GARDEN, IN COTONOU,BENIN - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN TANDOORI)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(717, 15, 54, 1720, 'Zou', 'Benin', 'ABOMEY', 'landscape-2017966_640.jpg', 'landscape-2017966_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Probably founded in the early 17th century, it soon became the capital of the kingdom of Abomey, which dominated production and trade with the European enterprises on the Slave Coast until the late 19th century. The town is located in an area where palm nuts and peanuts are grown it is connected by road and rail to Cotonou, the country&rsquo;s main commercial centre, and to Porto Novo, the capital. The royal palaces, the tombs of the kings, and a historical museum are maintained in Abomey the royal palaces were designated a UNESCO World Heritage site in 1985. Abomey, 144 kms northwest of Cotonou, was the capital of the fierce Dahomey Kingdom and force colonial powers had to reckon with for centuries. Its winding lanes dotted with palaces and temples, Abomey is shrouded with a palpable historical aura and filled with character.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are a few motels in town, but none are of particularly good quality. The best option is to stay at Cotonou.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air </strong>- One must fly in to Cotonou International Airport and take a taxi to Abomey.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Bus</strong> - From the Porto Novo auto gare, there are buses and taxis to Abomey and Lagos, Nigeria.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Boat</strong> - There are pirogues leaving from Porto arriving less visited lake villages nearby. Ask around down by the lagoon, about 50 mts east of the bridge for prices.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Road</strong> - Another option is to catch a bus or train from Cotonou to Bohicon, and use bush taxis for the remainder of the trip.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Getting Around</strong> - Zemi johns are a popular, cheap and efficient way to get around. They are simply a scooter like taxi popular in the country.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1- ABOMEY,BENIN&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;- [FAMOUS FOR VARZA A LA CLUZ IS A RICE DISH MADE FROM MEAT, PUCKLED CABBAGE, TOMATO SAUCE AND RICE ; ABLO IS A CORNMEAL BREAD MADE FROM RICE FLOUR, CORN FLOUR,YEAST, SALT AND SUGAR]&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(718, 15, 54, 310, 'Oueme', 'Benin', 'PORTO NOVO', 'africa-1803109_640.jpg', 'africa-1803109_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Porto Novo is the capital of Benin. Benin&rsquo;s second largest city of approximately 250000 people is a nice change of pace from the bustling Cotonou and has many nice features. It is an easy one hour car ride from Cotonou, and only 20 minutes from the beach. Porto Novo, named by the Portuguese in the 1500s, is still today showing significant Portuguese influence. For its size, Porto Novo has quite of bit of culture and tourist attractions. Nestling on the shores of Lake Nokoue, Porto Novo is Benin&#39;s unlikely capital. Its leafy streets, wonderful colonial architecture, unperturbed pace and interesting museums are in striking contrast to full on Cotonou. The Portuguese named the city after Porto when they established a slave trading post here in the 16th century.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are budget hotels, mid range hotels and splurge available in the city which are comfortable, with air conditioned rooms overlooking the lagoon in the western part of town. The splurge are the most expensive but nicer than the others.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- The city is located about 40 kilometres away from Cotonou Airport which has flights to major cities in West Africa and Europe.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- In 2016, Porto Novo is to be served by an extension of the Benirail train system.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Minibuses and taxis go to Cotonou regularly and are cheap. Tourists will most likely end up at the big market Dantopka in Cotonou unless they choose to descend somewhere before that. It can be quite intimidating getting out there especially in peak times.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Boat</strong> - There are pirogues leaving from Porto arriving less visited lake villages nearby. Ask around down by the lagoon, about 50 mts east of the bridge for prices. No fixed prices, but usually expect to pay around 2000 CFA round trip.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - Traffic isn&#39;t overwhelming like in Cotonou. However, like Cotonou, the best way and easiest way to see Porto Novo is by zemidjan.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - PORTO NOVO - [FAMOUS FOR ACARAJE IS A DISH MADE FROM BLACK PEELED BEANS FORMED INTO A BALL THEN FRIED IN PALM OIL ; ALLOCO IS A SNACK MADE FROM FRIED PLANTAIN AND SERVED WITH CHILLI PEPPER AND ONIONS ; FUFU IS A FOOD MADE FROM CASSAVA AND GREEN PLANTAIN FLOUR ; AMIVO IS A DISH MADE FROM CHICKEN, TOMATO PUREE, ONION AND PEPPERS AND SERVED WITH A SAUCE ; GARRI IS A FOOD MADE FROM CASSAVA TUBERS]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '');
INSERT INTO `city` (`id`, `continent_id`, `country_id`, `state_id`, `state_name`, `country_name`, `ci_name`, `main_image`, `main_image1`, `description`, `accomdation`, `transportation`, `eatable`, `experience_type_id`) VALUES
(720, 17, 55, 1890, 'Oropeza', 'Bolivia', 'SUCRE', 'medina-beach-192739_640.jpg', 'medina-beach-192739_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The constitutional capital of Bolivia, Sucre has a well preserved historic center, with many buildings dating back to the city&#39;s founding in the 16th century. As a World Heritage Site, Sucre abides by strict development rules, helping the city to retain its impressive views, buildings, and character. Sightseeing in Sucre reveals a distinctly Spanish style and form, though the colors of indigenous dress and art permeate the look of the city. Situated in a valley and surrounded by scenic mountains, the climate in town remains temperate and mild, perfect for walking tours. Proud, genteel Sucre is Bolivia&rsquo;s most beautiful city and the symbolic heart of the nation. It was here that independence was proclaimed, and while La Paz is now the seat of government and treasury, Sucre is recognized in the constitution as the nation&rsquo;s capital. A glorious ensemble of whitewashed buildings sheltering pretty patios, it&rsquo;s a spruce place that preserves a wealth of colonial architecture. Sensibly, there are strict controls on development, which have ensured Sucre remains a real showpiece of Bolivia. It was declared a Unesco World Heritage site in 1991.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The touristic appeal of Sucre has driven up demand for accommodations now slotted in old, colonial era buildings rather than new build high rises. This development ethos has worked well, with lodgings in Sucre&#39;s center among the most comfortable and characterful in the country. Exclusive options cluster around the town&#39;s prettiest plazas, with grand rooms and fine dining restaurants. Budget minded visitors should explore the range of guesthouses, set in modest formerly residential buildings on the town&#39;s side streets.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Located in the municipality of Yamparaez, 25 kms to the South of Sucre, Alcantari International Airport is around 30 kilometres from the city centre with an estimated travel time of around 40 minutes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Most long distance connections to and from Sucre operate from its main bus station, located 2 kms from the city centre. The easiest way to get to and from Sucre&rsquo;s bus terminal is by taxi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around </strong>- Sucre is a small town with regular hop on buses and plentiful taxis. A tourist bus or private transport is needed to visit some of the attractions outside of Sucre, such as Tarabuco market and the dinosaur footprints.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - SUCRE - [FAMOUS FOR PIQUE A LO MACHO IS A FOOD CONSISTING PIECES OF BEEF, POTATOES AND MIXTURE OF ONIONS, LOCOTO, BOILED EGGS, MUSTARD AND SAUCE ; MONDONGO IS A DISH MADE FROM FRIED PORK, POTATOES AND A RED CHILLI SAUCE ; CHORIPAN IS A TYPE OF SANDWICH FILLED WITH CHORIZO ; PLATO PACENO IS A SNACK COMBINATIO OF CORN, LIMA BEANS, POTATO AND FRIED CHEESE ; SANDWICH DE CHOLA IS A SANDWICH FILLED WITH ROASTED PORK, VEGETABLES AND A CHILLI SAUCE ; MAJADITO IS A RICE DISH SERVED WITH DRIED BEEF, FRIED EGGS, BEANS AND FRIED BANANA ; BUNUELOS IS A FRIED DOUGH BALL SNACK ; TUCUMANAS IS A TYPE OF PASTRY MADE FROM MEAT, VEGETABLES, BOILED EGGS AND SAUCE]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - SUCRE, AT MERCADO CENTRAL - (FAMOUS FOR FRUIT SALAD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - TROPICAL, IN SUCRE - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN SALAD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(721, 17, 55, 1889, 'Pedro Domingo Murillo', 'Bolivia', 'LA PAZ', 'la-paz-458029_640.jpg', 'la-paz-458029_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Set against a striking backdrop of snow capped mountains, Nuestra Senora de La Paz, commonly known as La Paz, is Bolivia&rsquo;s third most populous city and the world&rsquo;s highest seat of government. Juxtaposed with the colourful lifestyle and traditions of the Aymara people, is a cosmopolitan city full of modern cafes, museums, clubs, bars and restaurants. One of the highest cities in the world, La Paz is best explored at a slow pace, taking the time to soak up the city&rsquo;s rich culture and fascinating history. With its numerous fascinating sights, free events, and cool places to go out, La Paz truly is an amazing city to visit and explore. At 3650 mts above sea level, Bolivia&#39;s capital stands out as the world&#39;s highest altitude administrative centre. The experience gets even more giddying as one traverse the busy metropolis on its most iconic form of public transport the cable car system. At ground level, a tour of La Paz allows to admire a blend of traditional architecture, administrative buildings, and trendy new hangouts. Pack warm clothes, as the high altitude city experiences chilly evenings year round.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Growing popularity among backpackers and young travellers has led to an increase in budget accommodations in La Paz. The central neighborhoods of Santa Barbara and Juan XIII offer both low cost options and high end hotels. For a bohemian twist on a Paz vacation, stay in Sopocachi, the city&#39;s artsy neighbourhood.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Located in El Alto, La Paz&rsquo;s international airport is the highest airport in the world at 4058 mts. The distance between El Alto Airport and the centre of La Paz is around 20 kilometres with an estimated travel time of around 30 minutes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - The main bus terminal is in Central Park, near the upper end of the Prado and a 15-20 min walk from most hostels. From this bus station, buses leave for big cities such as Cochabamba, Santa Cruz, Oruro, Potosi, Sucre, Tarija and Arica. Buses leaving La Paz usually stop in El Alto to pick up more passengers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around </strong>- Transport within La Paz is safe and reliable. Traveling anywhere by taxi within the city centre and local buses are cheaper. There is also the option to take the Cable Car which is a fun way to see the city. As in any city, make sure to only take marked taxis and avoid walking by self at night.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - LA-PAZ - [FAMOUS FOR CHOLA SANDWICH &nbsp;MADE FROM PORK ; FOR SALTENAS IS A SAVORY PASTRIES FILLED WITH BEEF, PORK OR CHICKEN MIXED IN SAUCE AND SOMETIMES ALSO CONTAINS PEAS, EGGS, RAISINS, POTATOES AND OTHER INGREDIENTS ; CHURRASCO &nbsp;IS A GRILLED MEAT DISH ; MILANESA IS A BREADED OR FRIED SLICE OF BEEF OR CHICKEN AND SERVED WITH RICE AND SALAD ; PICANTE DE POLLO IS A SPICY CHICKEN MEAL SERVED WITH RICE, SALAD AND PARSLEY ; &nbsp;SAICE IS A DISH OF SPICY MINCED MEAT WITH RICE AND PEAS ; LAUCHAS &nbsp;IS A PIZZA OF DOUGH PASTRIES FILLED WITH CHEESE SAUCE ;&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - VAGON DEL SUR, LOCATED AT &nbsp;AVE., LOS SAUCES - (FAMOUS FOR BOLIVIAN &nbsp;CUISINE)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(722, 17, 55, 1888, 'Cordillera', 'Bolivia', 'SANTA CRUZ', 'DA12.jpg', 'DA13.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Set among the steamy, tropical lowlands just beyond the last Andean foothills, Santa Cruz is Bolivia&rsquo;s economic powerhouse. An isolated frontier town until the middle of the twentieth century, the city has since become the biggest in the country, a sprawling metropolis with a booming oil, gas, timber, cattle and agro industry economy. This rapid growth and the availability of land has attracted a diverse range of immigrants to Santa Cruz, including Japanese rice farmers, German speaking Mennonites and, far poorer, indigenous migrants from the Andes. Santa Cruz may surprise you with its small town feeling, colonial buildings and a lightly buzzing, relaxed tropical atmosphere. Bolivia&rsquo;s largest city oozes modernity yet clings stubbornly to tradition. The city center is vibrant and thriving, its narrow streets crowded with suited businessmen sipping chicha a fermented corn drink at street stalls, while taxis jostle with horses and carts for pole position at traffic lights. Locals still lounge on the main square listening to camba music, restaurants close for siesta and little stores line the porch fronted houses selling cheap, local products.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Accommodations in Santa Cruz lie within the limits of the Cuarto Anillo, while the areas outside of the ring road remain largely residential. The north of Barrio Equipetrol houses the city&#39;s glitziest and most luxurious hotels, offering extensive lists of amenities, including popular fine dining restaurants, swimming pools, and spas. Head closer to the center of town for more budget friendly options, including no frills hotels, pleasant guesthouses set in formerly residential buildings, and backpacker friendly hostels.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Viru Viru International Airport is Bolivia&#39;s largest and most modern airport and a hub for BoA. International flights on BoA travel to Madrid, Sao Paulo, and Buenos Aires with other destinations on the horizon.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- The death train, so named because of its history in transporting Yellow Fever victims, runs on bumpy tracks from Puerto Quijarro, close to Corumba on the Brazilian side. There is a variety of different trains offering different classes and prices. The journey takes 24 hours.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - There are many bus companies from another cities, like Cochabamba, La Paz, Sucre, Trinidad, that go to Santa Cruz de la Sierra. Tourists can arrive from La Paz in about 18 hrs, and it takes about 10 hrs from Cochabamba.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - LA GAIRA, LOCATED AT SANTA CRUz DE LA SIERRA - (FAMOUS FOR PATACONES IS A TYPE OF SIDE DISH MADE FROM UNRIPE PLANTAINS, OIL AND SALT)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - BOULEVARD PLAZA, LOCATED AT SUCRE 8, SANTA CRUZ DE LA SIERRA - (FAMOUS FOR KEBAB AND CHCKEN)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - ANTOJITOS MAR&iacute;A BELEN, LOCATED AT PLATANILLOS 119, SANTA CRUZ DE LA SIERRA, (FAMOUS FOR FRUIT JUICES AND &nbsp;PASTRIES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - CASA VEGANA,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT SARMIENTO SANTA CRUZ DE LA SIERRA - (FAMOUS FOR BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - SANTA CRUZ - {FAMOUS FOR CHARQUICAN IS A DISH MADE FROM CH&#39;ARKI OR BEEF, POTATOES, PUMPKIN, ONION, PEAS AND CORN ; PIQUE MACHO IS A FOOD CONSISTS THE BEEF, FRY POTATOES AND A &nbsp;MIXTURE OF ONIONS, LOCOTO, EGGS, MAYONNAISE, AND KETCHUP. ; LECHE ASADA IS A DESERT MADE FROM CONDENSED MILK}</strong></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(723, 17, 55, 1887, '', 'Bolivia', 'COCHABAMBA', 'cochabamba-2075202_1280.jpg', 'cochabamba-2075202_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Cochabamba sprawls out at the base of its own plain presented by the folds and contours of the Altiplano and the Andes. Almost midway between Santa Cruz and La Paz, this nature friendly neighbourhood and dramatic geographical location make for a fine balance of urban living and outdoor pursuits. Inhabited for over a thousand years, the department of Cochabamba is one of Bolivia&rsquo;s most understated regions. Cochabamba is a wonderful destination in its own right, featuring beautiful year round weather, stunning nature reserves, ancient archaeological sites as well as a colourful and dynamic culture which prides itself on its local cuisine. Cochabamba is the commercial hub of the country&rsquo;s richest agricultural region, the Cochabamba Valley. Named the city of eternal spring, it enjoys sunny climate that is matched by the warmth and openness of its population. The city&rsquo;s name is derived from the word khocha pampa meaning swampy plain. Cochabamba remains a very affordable city with prices far below those in Sucre or La Paz. An ideal alternative for anyone wishing to escape the crowd of South America&#39;s more popular destinations, Cochabamba vacations allow tourists to discover how Bolivians live on an everyday basis.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Beachside stays remain popular, with chic, boutique style hotels and larger high rise options offering extensive views of South America&#39;s largest lake. Expect to pay a little less when you look a few streets back from the sand and the water, with hotels and hostels both available. Thanks the Cochabamba&#39;s continuous uphill slope, views of the lake are possible from pretty much anywhere around the main urban area.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\n<strong>By Air</strong> - Cochabamba is the hub of the new airline Boliviana de Aviacion and as such has good, inexpensive connections to domestic and international destinations, including Buenos Aires and Sao Paulo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - The best roads into and out of Cochabamba city leads to La Paz, Oruro and Santa Cruz. It is also possible to travel to and from Potosi and Sucre by bus, but because of long, winding mountain roads at very high altitudes, the trip is uncomfortable and should be avoided.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - Most transport to towns within the department leave from certain distinct spots within the city of Cochabamba. They go whenever full, and are usually available throughout the day. Services to Tarata and Cliza leave from Avenida Barrientos, south of La Cancha marketplace.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - COCHABAMBA - [FAMOUS FOR SILPANCHO IS A DISH MADE FROM MEAT, RICE, POTATO, TOMATO, ONION, BEET, PARSLEY(HERB) AND TOPPED WITH EGGS ; FOR SALCHIPAPAS IS A TYPE OF FAST FOOD DISH MADE FROM FRENCH FRIES, BEEF SAUSAGES, SAUCE AND CHILLI PEPPERS ; &nbsp;FILLET(BONELESS MEAT OR FISH) WITH PALENTA IS A DISH OF BOILED CORNMEAL]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - CENTRO TURISTICO LAGUNA ESPERANZA, LOCATED AT CARRETERA VILLA TUNARI KM 82 - (FAMOUS FOR CHICHARRON IS A DISH MADE FROM CHICKEN, MUTTON, BEEF OR PORK)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - BIG JOY, LOCATED AT BENI 508 - (&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;FAMOUS FOR FRIED CHICKEN WINGS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - WISTUPIKU, LOCATED AT AV., MELCHOR PEREZ DE OLGUIN - (FAMOUS FOR EMPANADA IS ASTUFFED BREAD OR PASTRY MADE FROM MEAT, CHEESE, CORN SMUT OR OTHER INGREDIENTS)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(724, 15, 56, 1729, '', 'Botswana', 'GABORONE', 'botswana-970276_640.jpg', 'botswana-\r\n\r\n970276_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Once proudly referred to as Africa&rsquo;s fastest growing city, Botswana&rsquo;s capital, Gaborone, has been since its inception continually expanding, to the point that now the sprawling urban centre of some 300000 residents has become nearly unrecognisable from the tiny, dusty administrative town it was at the country&rsquo;s independence in 1966. The city of Gaborone is the largest in Botswana and also its capital. The modern buildings of Gaborone set against the tropical backdrops of this African nation are an unusual sight and despite its size, there are not too many reasons to visit the city. From the end of the 19th century, until 1963, tiny Gaberones Village, as the town was then called, consisted of only a small settlement on the railway line and a small administrative centre in the area now called The Village. The land between both settlements was Crown land, but was used by the people of the neighbouring village of Tlokweng as a cattle grazing area. Depending on the perspective Gaborone is one of Africa&#39;s more peaceful capital cities.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Gaborone compares to South Africa in terms of accommodation choice and costs. There are a handful of large chain hotels offering conference facilities, evening restaurants, gyms and bars and dozens of smaller guesthouses, lodges and bed &amp; breakfasts varying in quality, cleanliness and price.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- The nearest airport to Gaborone is Sir Seretse Khama Airport in Gaborone which is about 3 kms away from Gaborone city centre.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- The railway station in Gaborone is located south of the Parliament House in the city&#39;s centre. Railway served the founding purpose of the city bisecting the city in a north south direction.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Highways in and around Gaborone include the Trans Kalahari Highway, A1 Highway, and the Cairo Cape Town Highway. There are five major roads in Gaborone that go to Lobatse, Kanye, Molepolole and Tlokweng.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around </strong>- Public taxis in the city are generally small white cars and can be identified by their blue license plates. There are also several cab companies in Gaborone and many display contact information on the cab itself. Combis that are white vans and look like mini buses and buses are also available.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - CHUTNEY INDIAN RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT WEST GATE MALL - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;DOSA, &nbsp;IDLY, MANGO LASSI AND BUTTER CHICKEN]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - CARAVELLA PORTUGUESE RESTAURANT,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT PLOT &nbsp;421 MOKGOSI CLOSE OFF INDEPENDENCE AVENUE - [FAMOUS FOR CALDO VERDE IS A Green Soup MADE FROM SPINACH AND POTATO, &nbsp;VEGETABLE CURRY PREPARED IN WINE CURRY SAUCE SERVED WITH RICE, &nbsp;TOMATO RICE IS A RICE DISH SERVED WITH SALAD]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - NANDO&#39;S CBDB, AT WESTERN COMMERCIAL ROAD, THE SQUARE MALL, CBD - [FAMOUS FOR GRILLED CHICKEN IN SPICY CHILLI SAUCE]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - CAFE DIJO, LOCATED AT KGALE HILL ROAD - [FAMOUS FOR CARROT CAKE]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - DELI&#39;S, LOCATED IN THE CRAFT CENTRE - [FAMOUS FOR PASTAS, PIZZA AND MILKSHAKES]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - CAFE FEGO, AT 4TH COMMERCIAL CBD, &nbsp;(FIRST FLOOR OF WHITE TOWER IN THE SQUARE MALL) - [FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN PASTA DISH AND CHOCOLATE CAKE]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - MUGG AND BEAN, LOCATED IN GAME CITY - [FAMOUS FOR BURGERS AND SANDWICHES]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - MOKOLODI RESTAURANT, AT MOKOLODI NATURE RESERVE - [FAMOUS FOR PIZZA AND ICE COLD BEER]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>9 - SIMPLY ASIA, LOCATED AT RIVERWALK SHOPPING COMPLEX - [FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN COCONUT SOUP AND VEGETABLES CURIES]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>10 - HEALTH GENERATION, LOCATED AT AIRPORT - [FAMOUS FOR FRESH &nbsp;FRUIT JUICES]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>11 - GABORONE - [FAMOUS FOR SEWWAA IS A MEAT DISH MADE OF BEEF AND GOAT MEAT ; MAGWINYA IS A DISH MADE FROM FLOUR]</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(725, 15, 56, 1886, '', 'Botswana', 'MAUN', 'chobe-\r\n\r\n1712232_640.jpg', 'chobe-1712232_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Maun is the administrative centre of Ngamiland district and the seat of power of the Batawana people. Maun is the point of entry into the Okavango Delta and often into Botswana with direct flights from both Johannesburg and Gaborone. Spread out along the broad banks of the Thamalakane River, Maun retains an old world feel in spite of modern developments like sleek shopping malls and bank headquarters blend with rural huts, while cattle graze on the fertile riverside fields. Maun vacation makes a great base for hiking, safaris, and sightseeing. The hotels, restaurants and tourist amenities here are some of the best in the country due to the fact that the city is the main tourist stop in the country. The town itself does not have much going but it still attracts a wide range of people from luxury safari travellers to volunteers. There are some great campsites that are located by the river, providing a great place to stay for a few nights.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are a couple of hotels and some impressive guest houses in Maun. A number of campsites and hotels popular among travellers are clustered on the road to Moremi and Shorobe. Campsites popular with the budget conscious crowd are plentiful while affordable backpacker style lodges often offer on-site bars and restaurants.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air</strong> - Air Botswana operates regular services to Maun and Johannesburg. The airport passenger terminal is right in town, about two blocks from the major shopping centre.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Bus</strong> - There are daily buses from the bus rank in Gaborone to Maun. The ticket payment is collected right on the bus. The buses on major routes are pretty nice compared to many other African countries.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Tourists can get to Maun using the highway from Francistown. From Nata tourists have to follow National highway A3 which is very well sign posted.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Getting Around </strong>- There are various transport services like taxis, combis (vans) and local buses to travel around the city. Private cab services are also available within the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - PIZZA PLUS COFFEE AND CURRY, LOCATED AT AIRPORT ROAD - [FAMOUS FOR BURGERS AND CHICKEN TIKKA MASALA]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - WAX APPLE AND THE RED MONKEY, LOCATED AT AIRPORT ROAD - [FAMOUS FOR BEEF BURGER]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - TANDURI INDIAN RESTAURANT, &nbsp;LOCATED AT MOETI ROAD - [FAMOUS FOR NORTH INDIAN CUSINES]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - WIMPY, PLOT &nbsp;1196 SHOP C1, ENGEN SHOPPING CENTRE - [FAMOUS FOR BURGERS, MIXED GRILLS OR FISH &nbsp;&#39;N&#39; CHIPS]</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(726, 15, 56, 1885, '', 'Botswana', 'KASANE', 'botswana-\r\n\r\n1652902_640.jpg', 'botswana-1652902_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Set on the south bank of the Chobe River and facing Caprivi Strip to the north Kasane is a city in the Okavango Chobe region at the north eastren corner of Botswana. Kasane is a tourist hub and a jump off point for Chobe National Park and Victoria Falls. The town&rsquo;s own attractions include a huge Baobab tree that was once used as a prison due to its trunk that is so large a human can enter. There is also a snake park that houses around 50 snakes from 17 different species and is also wonderfully situated for exploring the Chobe River. Situated on the banks of the Chobe River Kasane is the administrative centre of Chobe district. Kasane briefly obtained international fame as the location of the remarriage of Elizabeth Taylor to Richard Burton, in 1975. Chobe Crocodile Farm is a great tourist attraction located approximately 8 kilometres to the east of Kasane in the small village of Kazungula. Kasane also boasts small shopping malls where all basic commodities can be purchased, and arts and crafts shops.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kasane is dominated by the large, riverfront hotels that cater to package safari guests. For those wanting to stay in Kasane town the mid range places are a better option. Tourists have to book lodges well in advance as the season for campsites mostly results in overbooked accommodations. For travellers wishing to stay and enjoy the park there are some hotels splendidly situated with wonderful views of the river and its wildlife.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Kasane International Airport has a few scheduled flights service to Gaborone and Maun. Many of the charter operators from Maun will also accept charters to or from Kasane.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- There is a paved road entering Kasane from the east and south from Nata, which connects to paved roads from Victoria Falls and within Botswana from Francistown, Maun, and Gaborone.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water</strong> - Nearby Kazungula has a ferry leading to Zambia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - There is not much public transport in Kasane. There are share taxis between Kasane and Kazungula. There are combis and some taxis available to travel within the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - HUNTERS PUB AND GRILL, LOCATED BEHIND SPAR - [FAMOUS FOR CAPPUCCINO IS A TYPE OF COFFEE DRINK PREPARED WITH DOUBLE ESPRESSO, MILK]<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - PEGGY&#39;S KITCHEN, IN KASANE - [FAMOUS FOR FRIED CHICKEN AND BAKED POTATO]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - CURRY COFFEE PIZZA PLACE, LOCATED AT MAIN STREET, PLOT 81 HUNTERS AFRICA COMPLEX - [FAMOUS FOR BUTTER CHICKEN BIRYANI]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(728, 16, 41, 387, 'Ontario', 'Canada', 'BRANTFORD', 'alexander-graham-bell-homestead-1188265_640.jpg', 'alexander-graham-bell-homestead-1188265_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Situated along the picturesque Grand River, Brantford has countless experiences waiting to be discovered and a multitude of attractions and events that are sure to engage and entertain. The city of Brantford is located in the heart of Southern Ontario with direct access to highway 403 and close proximity to other major highways rail lines and three major Canadian ports of entry Windsor, Toronto and Niagara Falls. Brantford is also known as telephone city as it was here in 1874 where Alexander Graham Bell first conceived the idea for the telephone. Brantford was named for Captain Joseph Thayendanegea Brant a Mohawk leader who led the Six Nations People from upper New York State to the Grand River basin where they established their village in 1784. The city of Brantford is host to some of the longest running festivals in Canada. Whether wanting cultural experiences, outdoor adventure, fantastic family fun, sporting events or culinary delights tourists will find it all in Brantford.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Brantford has everything from four star luxury hotels to clean and comfortable motor inns to suit every type of traveller and budget. With its great location, Brantford is really a spring in the middle of everything one wants to see or do. For the city lovers, tourists can pick from a number of great accommodations in Brantford that are close to restaurants, nightlife, shopping centres, museums and sport arenas.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - John C. Munro Hamilton International Airport in Hamilton is located about 35 kms east of Brantford. Brantford Municipal Airport located west of the city hosts an annual air show featuring the Snowbirds.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- The train station located just north of downtown Brantford has daily passenger trains on the Quebec City and also stop at Union Station in Toronto.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- Brantford Transit bus service serves the city with regular routes operating on schedule from the downtown Transit Terminal on Darling Street. Greyhound Canada has intercity service to Toronto, Hamilton, London, Windsor and other cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Brantford is connected with cities like Hamilton, Woodstock, Cambridge and Simcoe through highway 403 and 24.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - CARVIN, AT 122 KING ST. - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;BURGERS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - JOY SUSHI BAR, AT 195 HENRY ST. - (FAMOUS FOR SOUPS AND ROLLS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - WACKY WINGS, AT 141 KING GEORGE ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR CHEESECAKE AND PORK SANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - ZAZA&#39;S PIZZERIA INC, AT 155 LYNDEN ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - THE KITCHEN, AT 72 COLBORNE ST. E. - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;SANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - THE WORKS GOURMET BURGER BISTRO, AT 80 DALHOUSIE ST. - (FAMOUS FOR HAMBURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - SUNSET GRILL, AT 50 MARKET ST. S - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;OMELETTE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - TAAL FINE INDIAN CUISINE, AT 578 COLBORNE ST. E - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;CHICKEN CORN SOUP AND PANEER PAKORA( COTTAGE CHEESE WITH DEEP FRIED)]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>9 - SYMPOSIUM CAFE, AT 58 KING GEORGE ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR GRILLED CHICKEN SANDWICH)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>10 - BEN&#39;S KITCHEN AND BAR, AT 300 KING GEORGE ROAD - [FAMOUS FOR PHILLY BURGER ( TOPPED WITH SAUTEED ONIONS, GREEN PEPPERS AND CHEESE)]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>11 - BURFORD BAKERY, AT 127 KING ST. - (FAMOUS FOR CHEESE SANDWICH AND CAKES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>12 - PALACE SUBMARINE, AT 308 COLBORNE ST. - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>13 - NANKING, AT 71 CHARING CROSS ST. - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN FRIED RICE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>14 - ADMIRAL SUBMARINE, AT 55 DALHOUSIE ST. - (FAMOUS FOR MUSHROOM BURGERS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>15 - BROASTER&#39;S CRISPY FRIED CHICKEN, AT 26 BRANTWOOD PARK ROAD - [FAMOUS FOR FRIED CHICKEN, COLE SLAW ( IS A TYPE OF SALAD), AND CHICKEN ROTI]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>16 - YONG GREAT WALL BUFFET, AT 82 KING GEORGE ROAD - [FAMOUS FOR EGG ROLLS AND SPRING ROLLS]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>17 - SAN &nbsp;FRANOS CARRY OUT LTD, AT 95 CHARING ST. - (FAMOUS FOR HOTDOGS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>18 - ARBY&#39;S, AT 129 KING GEORGE ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN BACON SWISS SANDWICH, CHOCOLATE SHAKES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>19 - LONNIES, AT 42 MARKET ST. - (FAMOUS FOR CHILLI CHEESE FRIES AND BURGERS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>20 - JOHNNY BE GOOD DINER, AT 440 PARIS ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR ICE-CREAMS AND MILKSHAKES)<br />\r\nWEST GARDEN&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;560 WEST ST.,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;FAMOUS FOR EGG ROLLS AND CHOCOLATE BROWNIE</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(729, 17, 55, 1884, '', 'Bolivia', 'POTOSI', 'flamingos-\r\n\r\n2009559_640.jpg', 'flamingos-2009559_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Potosi is an attractive town in Southern Bolivia and is the ideal destination to experience Bolivian culture and history. Potosi has many old and active mines since it was once a major supplier of silver for the Spanish empire. Situated at an average elevation of 4090 mts above sea level Potosi gained its fame from below the ground. Today, the main attractions in Potosi remain its elegant glorious buildings and historical machinery. The town that once brought great wealth to South America&rsquo;s Spanish masters, Potosi is now hailed as a UNESCO World Heritage Site. Regarded for its charming history, ancient sights, stunning scenery and unique flora and fauna, Potosi&rsquo;s most sought attraction is Uyuni the largest salt flat in the world. It owes its existence to Cerro Rico, which rises dominatingly above the city to the south. Cerro Rico was the richest source of silver the world had ever seen. Potosi is a treasure store of colonial art and architecture that has more than two thousand colonial buildings many of which have been restored. Hundreds of town houses and mansions remain complete with red tiled roofs and decorative balconies.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Visitors can choose from a good selection of colonial era buildings housing charming hotels and welcoming guesthouses. Generally speaking, look to the south end of the centre for more budget friendly options, with little guesthouses located on residential side streets. By contrast, the more spacious area surrounding the train station has the majority of the grander hotels, set on impressive boulevards and overlooking central plazas.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- If arriving at Sucre airport, there are shared taxis that depart from the airport. From Sucre it is worth hiring a cab for 2 or more people as the trip is faster and more comfortable than one on a collective cab or a bus, and the cab leaves at schedule.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- There are 2 bus terminals in Potosi. The old terminal located on Ave. Universitaria, 30 minutes walk uphill to the city centre. Uyuni bound buses and shared taxi to Sucre leave from there. While the new terminal is located in the NE of the city and is accessible by a 30 minutes bus ride or taxi. Most long distance buses leave from there, as buses to Sucre.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around </strong>- Taxis are generally cheap and plentiful around Potosi. However, always check the price with the driver. Some charge per person which could get into arguments when it comes time to pay. Buses from Centro area to Main bus Terminal costs cheaper.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - MANZANA MAGICA, LOCATED AT 239, ORURO, VILLA IMPERIAL DE &nbsp;POTOSI - [FAMOUS FOR BURGERS AND FRESH FRUIT JUICES]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - EL FOGON, LOCATED IN POTOSI - [FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN SOUP AND CHICKEN SANDWICH]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - KOALA CAFE, AT 5, AYACUHO, &nbsp;VILLA IMPERIAL DE POTOSI - [FAMOUS FOR VEGGIE BURGER, BANANA CAKE AND SCHNITZEL (IS A MEAT DISH COATED WITH FLOUR BEATEN EGGS, BREAD, AND THEN FRIED IN OIL)]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - PIZZERIA EL MANA, LOCATED AT BUSTILLO, POTOSI&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;- [FAMOUS FOR VARIETIES OF PIZZA]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n5 - PHISQA WARMIS, CALLE SUCRE 55 - [FAMOUS FOR GRILLED CHICKEN AND LOCAL CUISINES]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n6 - LA TABERNA, CALLE JUNIN 12, VILLA IMPERIAL DE POTOSI - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;SPAGHETTI ( IS A TYPE OF PASTA MADE FROM MILLED WHEAT AND WATER ) AND CHICKEN WITH MUSHROOM WHITE WINE SAUCE]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n7 - CAFE DE LA PLATA, LOCATED AT PLAZA &nbsp;10 DE &nbsp;NOVIEMBRE - [FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;COFFEE AND SANDWICHES]<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n8 - CAFE PUB 4060, LOCATED IN POTOS - [FAMOUS FOR TACOS ( IS A DISH MADE OF CORN, MEAT, VEGETABLES AND CHEESE) AND CHICKEN WINGS]</strong></p>\r\n', ''),
(737, 17, 57, 406, 'Santiago', 'chile', 'SANTIAGO', 'santiago-de-compostela-1254880_1280.jpg', 'santiago-de-compostela-1254880_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Santiago the financial and business capital of Chile and serves as countries cultural and entertainment centre and is home to its best museums and galleries along with excellent shopping, dining and hotel options. Centrally located and the country&#39;s main transportation hub Santiago is the place where most visitors begin their Chilean travel before heading to the Andes or other areas of outstanding natural beauty. A tour of Santiago leads visitors through charming neighbourhoods each with its own look and feel and ideal place for exploration on foot. A range of nightlife opportunities draw a young crowd of international pleasure seekers, while the city&#39;s central location appeals to tourists interested in exploring the rest of the country from a comfortable urban base. Tourists can get round many of Santiago&rsquo;s attractions on foot in two to three days. A tour of the compact core centred on the bustling Plaza de Armas includes visit to Palacio de la Moneda, the excellent Museo Chileno de Arte Precolombino and Museo Colonial followed by a climb up to Cerro Santa Lucia.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Consider the hotels located in downtown area where one can find many furnished apartments ideal for longer stays for easiest access to the city&#39;s top museums and eateries. Santiago also features numerous distinct neighbourhoods filled with affordable sleeping options.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Comodoro Arturo Merino Benitez International Airport is Santiago&rsquo;s National Airport. Many airlines operate flight from various places.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- The bus ride between Santiago and Mendoza in Argentina has beautiful views and takes about eight hours and there are bus connections to all major destinations on the continent.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - Santiago has a metro system with many holding rotating art exhibitions. Buses are mostly modern and run around the clock on the main lines. Renting a car is also a very good option if wanting to get around Santiago and its surroundings.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - MULATO, LOCATED AT &nbsp;JOSE VICTORINO &nbsp;LASTARRIA, 307 - (FAMOUS FOR EMPANADA IS A TYPE OF BREAD OR PASTRY MADE BY DOUGH STUFFING, CONSISTS OF MEAT, CHEESE, HUITLACOCHE AND OTHER INGREDIENTS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - EL &nbsp;DIABLITO, LOCATED AT MERCED 336 - (FAMOUS FOR MICHELADA IS A RED BEER MADE FROM, LIME JUICE, and ASSORTED SAUCES, SPICES, AND PEPPERS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - OX RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT NUEVA COSTANERA 3960, VITACURA - (FAMOUS FOR LOMO SALTADO IS A DISH MADE FROM BEEF STEAK, ONIONS, TOMATOES AND FRENCH FRIES, SOY SAUCE, RICE, CHILLI PEPPERS AND CREMA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - EL HUERTO, LOCATED AT ORREGO LUCO 54, PROVIDENCIA - (FAMOUS FOR GAZPACHO IS A SOUP MADE FROM TOMATO, CUCUMBER AND GARLIC)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - FUENTE ALEMANA, LOCATED AT O&#39;HIGGINS A., LIBERTADOR &nbsp;BERNARDO 58 - (FAMOUS FOR SANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - COOL, LOCATED AT CONSTITUCION 6, PROVIDENCIA - (FAMOUS FOR CREPE IS A TYPE OF PANCAKE MADE FROM WHEAT FLOUR, MILK AND EGGS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - LA TERRAZA, LOCATED AT AVDA VICUNA MACKENNA 24, PROVIDENCIA - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN SOUP)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - LA FUENTE &nbsp;CHICA, LOCATED AT APOQUINDO OTE., &nbsp;7645, LAS CONDES - (FAMOUS FOR CHORRILLANA &nbsp;IS A DISH MADE FROM BEEF, FRENCH FRIES, ONION AND OTHER SPICES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>9 - DEPANA. CL, LOCATED AT &nbsp;NUNOA, METROPOLITAN REGION - (FAMOUS FOR CACHAPA IS A TYPE OF PANCAKE MADE FROM GROUND CORN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>10 - SANTAIGO - [FAMOUS FOR POROTOS GRANDOS &nbsp;IS A STEW MADE FROM POCHAS, SWEET CORN, PUMPKINS AND POTATOES ; CAZUELA IS A TYPE OF SOUP &nbsp;MADE FROM MEAT AND VEGETABLES ; CALDILLO DE CONGRIO &nbsp;IS A TYPE OF SOUP MADE FROM FISH HEADS(CONGRIO COLORADO), ONION, GARLIC, CORIANDER, CARROT, PEPPER, CREAM, TPMATOES AND POTATOES]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(738, 17, 57, 1883, '', 'chile', 'ARICA', 'chile-1681121_640.jpg', 'chile-1681121_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Known as the city of eternal spring because of its ideal warm and mild climate, the northern city of Arica is full of natural treasures. Beach and wildlife lovers, as well as the culturally enthusiastic traveller, will certainly appreciate this destination. Situated right along a coastal desert, surrounded by golden dunes and a breathtaking national park, Arica is a must see in Chile. As the northernmost city of Chile, Arica is close to Peru and was once the main port for Bolivian trade, which has given the city its own unique flair. Less organized than most Chilean cities, with hundreds of street vendors and markets, Arica boasts an attractive centre filled with pleasant gardens, sand dunes, and long sandy beaches. With a history that dates back ten thousand years, archaeologists have discovered that Arica was the centre of a number of pre-Colombian cultures. Arica is also the gateway to Lauca National Park, one of South America&rsquo;s true gems, with stunning snow capped peaks over 19,000 ft high, and a plethora of wildlife including vicunas and viscachas. Lauca is also home to one of the largest lakes in the world, Lago Chungara. Standing in this remote wilderness offers one new definitions of space and beauty. Venturing even further from the coast and into the city itself is just as rewarding, with an abundance of highlights and attractions to discover.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Beachgoers and adventurers&nbsp;will find suitable places to stay in Arica. Along the coast choose from resort style lodgings and pristine high rise hotels out from the main coastal roads. The town centre provides hotels and guesthouses ranging from simple to luxurious with grander options lining the main boulevards and simpler fare dotted along the side streets.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- The Aereopuerto Chacalluta Airport situated in the north of city handles all the domestic flights from all Chilean cities, as well as international flight to and from Peru and Bolivia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- The Pan American Highway connects Arica to Peru. Bus services are available from Santiago and Iquique. Taxis and car rentals are also available.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water</strong> - Arica is also the port of call for many cruise ships who offer day trips and city tours. There are ship services available from Port de Santos in Brazil to Port de Arica, Chile.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around </strong>- Walking will get tourists to most places in town, although numerous buses run along the major avenues for those in a hurry. They are also handy for getting to and from the bus station. Taxis and radio taxis are also an option.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - CLUB MAFRA, LOCATED AT TUCAPEL 196 - (FAMOUS FOR CHEESESANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - RESTAURANTE PURO CHILE, LOCATED AT PARINACOTA REGION - (FAMOUS FOR PASTEL DE CHOCLO IS A DISH MADE FROM SWEET CORN, FillED WITH BEEF, CHICKEN, RAISINS, OLIVES, ONION AND EGGS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - EL POLLON, LOCATED AT PANAMERICANA NORTE 2026-2048 - (FAMOUS FOR ARROZ CHAUFA IS A DISH CONSISTS A MIXTURE OF FRIED RICE WITH VEGETABLES, INCLUDING, ONIONS EGG AND MEAT)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - ARICA - [FAMOUS FOR MACHAS A LA PARMESANA IS A TYPE OF SEAFOOD DISH MADE FROM MACHAS (AKA PINK CLAMS), CHEESE, AND WHITE WINE ; COLA DE MONO OR &nbsp;COLEMONO IS A DRINK SERVED AROUND CHRISTIMAS TIME ; BARROS JARPA IS A TYPE OF SANDWICH MADE FROM HAM AND MELTED CHEESE]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(739, 17, 57, 1882, '', 'chile', 'PUCON', 'lake-1192698_640.jpg', 'lake-1192698_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Famous for its location between the massive Lake Villarica and the active Villarica Volcano, the small town of Pucon in southern Chile is a popular tourist destination for Chileans and international travellers alike. Pucon attracts those who enjoy action packed activities, including water activities on the lake, hiking through the Villarica National Park, skiing down the Villarica Volcano, and white water rafting down the Trancura River. Lake Villarrica, on the south bank of which lies the city, is one of the first links of the extensive chain of water mirrors that extend towards the southern zone of Chile. This is an interesting city to visit any time of the year. The region has two national parks the Huerquehue and the Villarrica. The latter is the home of the 2847 mts high volcano, one of the ten most active volcanoes in the world, which has permanent fumaroles that may be observed from the urban shell. In the winter, ski and other winter sports are practiced on its slopes. In the summer, adventurers may climb to its very crater. The Trancura River and its rapids, the hot springs and the cultural richness of the area turn Pucon into one of the most visited cities in southern Chile. This variety of environments invites visitors to practice water sports, mountaineering, horse riding, flora and fauna watching, fly-fishing and cultural tours among other activities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Despite of Pucon being a relatively small urban area, accommodation infrastructure here is well developed, ranging from backpacker hostels to luxury hotels. Pucon features a wide range of options when it comes to places to stay, though the bottom line for even budget prices is significantly higher than elsewhere in Chile. Many of the most affordable establishments are the hostels clustered in the city centre which often feature communal areas popular with the backpacker crowd.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Pucon&#39;s airport operates only during summer and the flights from Santiago are expensive. The closest airport for the remainder of the year is Temuco to which airlines do the flight in about one hour from Santiago or Puerto Montt.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - The road from the turn off from Santiago to Pucon is paved and in good shape. There are plenty of collectivo buses too and small public buses. Buses travel between Santiago and Pucon daily, many overnight.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - There are frequent daily buses from many cities in the country. From Temuco there are departures every half an hour. The majority of buses which come from Santiago, travel overnight</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Every night there is a train from Santiago to Temuco, which has three separate classes for travelling. From Temuco to Pucon there are several buses during the day, easily taken from the main Bus Terminal.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - PUCON - [FAMOUS FOR SOPA DE PATA IS A TYPE OF SOUP MADE FROM COW&#39;S FEET, TRIPE, YUCA, CHAYOTES, SWEET CORN, BANANAS AND GREEN BEANS ; HUMITA IS A DISH PREPARED WITH CORN, ONION, BASIL AND BUTTER OR LARD AND SERVED WITH SUGAR, CHILLE PEPPER, TOMATO, OLIVE AND PAPRIKA ; SOPAIPILLA IS A TYPE OF PASTRY MADE FROM WHEAT FLOUR) AND BUTTER ; CHUPE IS A TYPE OF STEW &nbsp;MADE FROM MEAT OF (CHICKEN, LAMB, BEEF OR OFFAL) OR SEAFOOD (SHRIMP, CRAYFISH, SHELFISH), VEGETABLES AND MILK OR CREAM ; ALFAJOR IS A TYPE OF SWEET PASTRY MADE FROM FLOUR, HONEY, ALMONDS AND HAZELNUTS ; PAN DE PASCUA IS A TYPE OF SWEET CAKE MADE FROM G HONEY, FRUITS, RAISINS, WALNUTS AND ALMONDS ; MOTE CON HUESILLO IS A NON-ALCHOLIC BEVERAGE MADE FROM DRIED PEACHES, SUGAR OR HONEY, CINNAMON AND WHEAT ;&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - EL POWDER, LOCATED AT &nbsp;GRAL. URRUTIA 520 - (FAMOUS FOR FRUIT JUICES)</strong></p>\r\n', '');
