(740, 17, 57, 1881, '', 'chile', 'IQUIQUE', 'beach-778243_640.jpg', 'beach-778243_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The city of Iquique is located in the first region of Chile know as the Tarapaca Region. Iquique is also the capital of the Tarapaca Region in Chile. Zofri or the Zona Franca makes this city the pillar of Chilean economy. This city is also called the Miami of Chile because of its clean, clear and warm water beaches with beautiful palm trees along the coast. Iquique is home to a lot of foreigners who make a living from Zofri. Iquique is also popular to Para gliders and Surfers who consider this city to be a great place for these sports. Iquique got its name from the Aymara word &quot;Iki&quot; which means sleep on the way, lot of people say that it&rsquo;s true of the feeling of tranquillity one feels in this amazing city. In the 19th century there was a mining boom in the Atacama Desert and this lead to the development of Iquique, leading to it now being a trendy city with casinos, gorgeous beaches and an array of bars and restaurants. Originally Iquique was a Peruvian town with a large Chilean population however it was officially made Chilean after the War of the Pacific. It is one of only two free ports in Chile today.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Hotels near the beach tend to stay relatively expensive throughout the year, so if visiting on a budget, consider one of the city&#39;s many hostels. Rental apartments distributed across Iquique accommodate visitors looking for more privacy and space.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Many flights from Iquique&#39;s Diego Aracena International Airport connect daily with Santiago and other main cities in the country. International flights connect it to Peru, Bolivia and Argentina.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Buses pull in from different locations of Chile and Argentina and the main terminal in Iquique is located in the north of the city. Few buses also operate from central Mercado.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Pan-Americana Highway connects Iquique to Santiago, Easter Island and many other cities of Chile.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around </strong>- Micros run along the major streets in the centre and take from the centre to the Zofri in no time. Walking is the most convenient mode of transport for getting to and from the beaches. One can get a shared taxi or get a private one for travelling around.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - IQUIQUE - [FAMOUS FOR LECHE ASADA IS A DESERT MADE WITH CONDENSED MILK ; MILCAO IS A DISH MADE FROM POTATOES, BUTTER AND VEGETABLE OIL ; COMPLETO IS A TYPE OF HOTDOG &nbsp;MADE FROM BREAD, SAUSAGE, TOMATO, AVOCADO, MAYONNAISE, SAUERKRAUT ; CHACARERO IS A TYPE OF SANDWICH MADE FROM &nbsp;BREAD, SLICED STEAK(MEAT) OR PORK WITH TOMATOES, GREEN BEANS AND CHILLI PEPPER ;&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - WAGON, LOCATED AT THOMPSON 85 - [FAMOUS FOR PESCADO A LA HUARA-HUARA IS A DISH OF FILET(BONELESS MEAT OR FISH) IN OLIVE OIL WITH CHILIES, CLOVE, ONIONS AND POTATOES]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - PUERTO CAMARON, LOCATED AT BAQUEDANO 801 - (FAMOUS FOR SHRIMP SALAD AND SHRIMP PASTA)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '9'),
(741, 17, 57, 1880, '', 'chile', 'EASTER ISLAND', 'easter-island-724795_640.jpg', 'easter-island-724795_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Officially a territory of Chile, Easter Island lays thousands of miles off the coast roughly halfway to Tahiti. This tiny volcanic island is only 164 sq kms in area and is almost lost in the endless blue of the Pacific Ocean. The island is famous for its 887 extant monumental statues called moai created by the early Rapanui people centuries ago. An excess of theories surround the origins and construction of these giant monolithic stone statues but the truth is that they are the legacy left behind by the Rapa Nui civilization that once inhabited the island. Tall figures carved out of volcanic rock between the 11th and 14th centuries by Polynesian settlers they have long unsmiling faces elegant hawk like noses and brooding brows. They can seem alienating or enthralling, depending on the angle, the light and the weather. Volcanic in origin it has several dead craters dotted over its sparsely covered surface one of which now contains a freshwater lake. The terrain on the treeless volcanic slopes is fairly grassy, but most of the island is covered in rugged lava fields. Easter Island also offers some great diving and surfing as well as two volcanic craters and several sandy beaches.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The main urban area on the island, Hanga Roa houses the vast majority of Easter Island&#39;s accommodations. While the number of choices remains pretty limited considering the island&#39;s popularity, the range of lodgings suits a variety of travellers, from budget conscious backpackers to those seeking luxury. Relaxed guesthouses and hostels provide decent rooms to get head down for the night after a long day&#39;s exploration.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The island is accessible by regular commercial air service to its Hanga Roa airport and Rapa Nui&rsquo;s Mataveri Airport. As a part of Chile, it is a domestic flight from Santiago and passports do not need to be presented on arrival when arriving from the Chilean mainland.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water</strong> - Easter Island is on a round the world voyage, in which it provides an interesting stop on the way between Polynesia and South America and will help bolster others perception. Due to the swell only one in four cruise ships can berth via tenders. If want to take the intrepid route, the tall ship Soren Larsen sails to Easter Island from New Zealand once a year. The voyage takes 35 days, crossing the point on earth furthest from land.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - Easter Island is relatively small, so it is possible to get around fairly easily, even though public transportation is not available. That of course is except for taxis, which are plentiful and very cheap. In fact, the flat rate pricing make taxis a great island bargain.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - EASTER ISLAND - [FAMOUS FOR CURANTO IS A FOOD CONSISTS SEAFOOD, MEAT, POTATOES AND VEGETABLES ; TUNU AHI IS A DISH &nbsp;MADE FROM FISH ; CEVICHE IS A SEAFOOD DISH MADE FROM FISH, LEMON, ONION AND CHILI PEPPER ;&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - ECO TAINA, LOCATED AT HANGA ROA - (FAMOUS FOR COFFEE, PIZZA AND CAKES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - MIKAFE, LOCATED AT HANGA ROA - {FAMOUS FOR SORBET IS A DESERT MADE FROM WATER, SUGAR, FLAVOURING WITH (FRUIT JUICES, WINE OR LIQUEROR AND HONEY)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - KANAHAU, LOCATED AT HANGA ROA - (FAMOUS FOR GNOCCHI IS A TYPE OF Dumpling MADE FROM POTATOES OR SEMOLINA OR WHEAT FLOUR OR BREADCRUMBS SOMETIMES CHEESE AND EGGS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - TIA BERTA, LOCATED AT ATAMU TEKANA, HANGA ROA - (FAMOUS FOR CHILE CON QUESO IS A DISH OF CHILI PEPPER AND MELTED CHEESE)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(742, 15, 64, 1711, '', 'Angola', 'LUANDA', 'baia-de-luanda-2345744_640_(1).jpg', 'baia-de-luanda-2345744_640_(1)1.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Luanda was founded by Portuguese explorer Paolo Dias de Novaes as St. Paul of Luanda in 1576. It became the capital of a Portuguese colony in 1586 and became the capital of independent Angola when the former Portuguese colony gained its independence in 1975. The city is located in the north western region of the country on the coast of the Atlantic Ocean. As major port city for Angola in the 16th century Luanda became the centre for commercial, political and cultural affairs. The Portuguese also used Luanda as their major slave trading port until 1836. Despite the violent past and clashing contrasts of Luanda, Angola&rsquo;s capital is something of a wild paradise waiting to be discovering. There are hidden pockets of wildlife to keep nature lovers immersed in the unkempt beauty and temperate climate of a previously unfamiliar destination that now stands proudly amongst the more celebrated ones.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are a range of options to choose from for hotels in Luanda for travellers visiting to Luanda, Angola. The prices are very high and the demand is even higher. At the same time the quality of the accommodation is usually lower than most foreigners&rsquo; expectations. The price for making accommodation in Luanda is an extremely expensive treat. Cheaper options like down market hotels are booked several months in advance.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Luanda International Airport in Luanda serves as a major airport with quite good number of national and international airline services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - There are a few short passenger lines, but they are not very safe. Angola once had the most extensive rail network in Africa while under colonial rule.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - The National Bus Service has just re-opened but routes are not organized yet. There are some local services in Luanda and in between cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- The main road for tourists will be the coastal highway leading north to the DRC and South to Namibia. Roads are one of the top priorities in reconstruction efforts including a handful of six lane highways leading out of the city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water</strong> - There are ferries operating from Luanda to the Cabinda exclave, it&rsquo;s useful to avoid a transit of the DRC and the journey takes about 14 hours.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - A popular means for tourists to get around the city is by mini bus taxis, easily identifiable by their pale blue and white.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - &nbsp;ART BURGER,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;AT 63, Av., CMTE., CHE GUEVARA - (FAMOUS FOR HAMBURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - CHURRASCARIA NANDINHOS, AT RUA COMANDANTE VALODIA 13 - (FAMOUS FOR GRILLED CHICKEN AND TAMOTO ONION SALAD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - GALERIA DOS PAES, RUA DOS TRANSMISORES - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;PIZZA AND CAKE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - FOURTH OF JULY RESTAURANT, AT &nbsp;Av., MURTALA MOHAMED (SPORTSMAN&#39;S HOUSE), CAPE ISLAND - [FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN SHAWARMA (PITA BREAD, STUFFED WITH CHICKEN BREAST CUBES ON PLATE WITH TAHINE SAUCE, SERVED WITH FRIED POTATO)]</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - MOMENTS, AT Av., CMTE. GIKA - (FAMOUS FOR SHRIMP &nbsp;CURRY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - BARBARICO, AT Av., CMTE., CHE GUEVARA - (FAMOUS FOR GRILLED CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - DAR EL &nbsp;AMIR, LOCATED IN &nbsp;LUANDA - (FAMOUS FOR HUMMUS IS A FOOD MADE FROM MASHED CHICKPEASOR OTHER BEANS, BLENDED WITH TAHINI, OLIVE OIL AND LEMON JUICE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - BE &nbsp;DELICIOUS, LOCATED AT 6, RUA DO ATLETICO - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;CHOCALATE ICE-CREAM)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(743, 15, 62, 1879, '', 'MAURITIUS', 'PORT LOUIS', 'water-1250090_640_(1).jpg', 'water-1250090_640_(1)1.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Located on the northwest coast of the island, Port Louis the capital city of Mauritius is characterized by its administrative importance as well as the liveliness of economic and commercial activities. Mauritius&rsquo;s vibrant port capital Port Louis encircled by the moody Moka Mountains on the northwest coast is a fascinating mix of old and new. Port Louis is really a place to wander, taking in the legacy of three centuries of colonialism and the influence of India and China along with a few interesting museums and religious sites. The bustle and glamour of the streets and the wonderfully preserved colonial buildings make Port Louis a must to explore on foot. Port Louis boasts eclectic architecture including French colonial buildings and historical monuments such as the 19th century Jummah Mosque and the St. James Cathedral. With Victorian warehouses and Creole bungalows with low verandas houses of worship for every major religion and busy markets the city has character stamped all over it.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Port Louis offers numerous home stays and guesthouses varying in degrees of affordability and luxury. Travellers with deep pockets can explore the high end resorts near the beachfront where amenities include air-conditioning, top quality restaurants, bars and on demand food and beverages. Midrange villas and bungalows along the main strip prove a viable option for those wanting a more independent jumping off point for exploring the region.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Sir Seewoosagur Ramgoolam International Airport is located in Plaine Magnien approximately 48 kms away from the city of Port Louis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - There are a number of bus services to Port Louis from nearby cities such as Cassis, Vallee-des-Pretres and Plaine Verte. There are two main bus stations in Port Louis, Victoria Station and Immigration Square. Both privately run and government run buses ply to Port Louis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - The roads and highways leading to Port Louis are in good condition. Hence, driving on the roads is never a problem except for traffic issues during peak hours.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water</strong> - Port Louis serves as Mauritius&rsquo;s main harbour and the country&rsquo;s official port of entry. Several cities across the world have cruise ships and passenger ferry services to Mauritius.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - Buses are the most preferred mode of transport in Port Louis, used extensively by locals and tourists alike. Cabs/taxis in Port Louis are priced slightly on the higher side. Tourists can also rent a car to get around the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - STAR DEG BRIANI, LOCATED AT ANGLE ET TRIANGLE, SIR SEEWOOSAGUR RAMGOOLAM - (FAMOUS FOR BEEF BIRYANI AND BIRYANI CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - MYSTIC MASALA SNACK BAR, LOCATED AT WATER FRONT - (&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;FAMOUS FOR MASALA DOSA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - KIMCHI HOUSE, LOCATED AT QUEEN ST., - (FAMOUS FOR BULGOGI IS A DISH MADE FROM BEEF OR PORK)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - BEER AND SPICE, LOCATED AT PORT LOUIS - (FAMOUS FOR FISH CURRY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - OCEAN VAGABOND, LOCATED AT &nbsp;LA GAULETTE - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA, PASTA, AND FISH FOOD)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n7 - DEWA &nbsp;AND SONS, LOCATED AT &nbsp;RUE L&#39;HOMME, ROSE HILL - (FAMOUS FOR DHOL PORI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - CHEZ ROSY, LOCATED AT GRIS GRIS, SOUILLAC - (FAMOUS FOR GRILLED LOBSTER, ROASTED CHICKEN, OCTPOUS CURRY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>9 - PORT LOUIS - [&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;FAMOUS FOR GAJAK IS A SNACK MADE FROM VEGETABLES AND BATTEREDIN CHICKPEA FLOUR WITH HERBS AND CHILLI ; ROUGAIL IS A DISH MADE FROM TOMATOES, GINGER, ONIONS, AND PEPPERS ; ALOUDA IS A SOFT DRINK MADE FROM MILK, SUGAR, TOUKMARIA, VANILLA AND ALMOND]</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(744, 15, 62, 1878, '', 'Mauritius', 'GRAND BAIE', 'beach-1955371_640.jpg', 'beach-1955371_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Grand Baie is without a doubt the most popular resort in Mauritius. Not so long ago it was a peaceful coastal village, it has now become the holiday capital of Mauritius. The town is located on the north coast of the island and has everything from designer boutiques and craft shops to gourmet restaurants and nightclubs. Grand Baie is the main centre for water sports including, sailing, waterskiing, windsurfing and kite-surfing. It is also the starting point for many island excursions, boat trips and dive cruises. The northern part of Mauritius is famous for its stunning white sand beaches and blue water lagoons. Trou Aux Biches has colourful reefs that can easily be reached from the shore making it popular with snorkelers. This pretty white sandy beach is a great place to relax in the shade of one of the many casuarinas trees. Some of the best tourist sites are located in the north including Port Louis the capital with its bustling market the charming fishing village of Cap Malheureux the wildlife of La Nicoliere and the famous Pamplemousses Botanical Gardens.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Grand Baie as the top holiday destination in Mauritius offers variety of hotels, guesthouses and private apartments and villas. There are many places to stay in and around Grand Bay including hotels, guest houses and villas that range from deluxe resorts to rooms to let. There are existing houses and villas that are available and several new developments are also under construction or have been recently finished.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - The drive from Grand Baie to Port Louis takes about 30 minutes while the drive to the airport takes about 1 hour and 30 minutes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Grand Baie has a good bus route leading to key locations in Mauritius. Tourists can easily get the bus from Grand Baie to Port Louis or to other cities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - CAFE MULLER&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT ROYAL ROAD B13 - (FAMOUS FOR CREPE IS A TYPE OF PANCAKE MADE FROM WHEAT FLOUR, MILK AND EGGS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - FRENCH BURGER, LOCATED AT GRAND BAIE - (FAMOUS FOR HOTDOG AND HAMBURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - DOMAINE, LOCATED AT THE VALE - (FAMOUS FOR CHILLI CHICKEN AND CHILLI LAMB)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - LA ROUGAILLE CREOLE, LOCATED AT ROYAL ROAD, NEAR SUNSET BOULEVARD - {FAMOUS FOR BOUILLABAISSE IS A DISH MADFE FROM &nbsp;(SCOTPIONFISH, SEA ROBIN, CONGER) HERBS AND SPICES}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 -ZORBAS, LOCATED AT ROYAL ROAD, NEAR POLICE STATION - (FAMOUS FOR BAKLAVA IS A SWEET PASTRY &nbsp;MADE FROM FILO DOUGH, NUTS AND HONEY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - BLUE LAGOON CAFE, LOCATED AT ROUTE ROYALE - {FAMOUS FOR PANINI IS A TYPE OF SANDWICH MADE FROM BREAD, FILLED WITH(SALAMI, HAM, CHEESE, MORTADELLA(SAUSAGE))}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - MAMMA MIA, LOCATED AT ROYAL ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR STEAK TARTARE IS A MEAT DISH MADE FROM RAW BEEF OR HORSEMEAT)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(745, 15, 62, 1877, '', 'Mauritius', 'CUREPIPE', 'collection-111082_640.jpg', 'collection-111082_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The city of lights or La Ville-Lumiere Curepipe is perched upon one of the highest plateaus of Mauritius. The town is famed for shopping and its dormant volcano Trou-aux-Cerfs, but there&rsquo;s more to Curepipe than just that. With a population nearing 100000 the town of Curepipe is the second biggest town in Mauritius. From colonial relics to beautiful gardens Curepipe has a lot to offer visitors. Lush landscapes stretch out as far as the eye can see in the rainy city of Curepipe. Its cooler temperatures compared with coastal regions thanks to its position in the rainy uplands in the centre of the island in the plains Curepipe gives some respite from the heat of the beaches. The Curepipe Botanic Garden is among the biggest attractions of the town.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Curepipe feature plenty of budget friendly and mid range accommodations found along the main strip or on the beachside. For more luxury options visitors tend to flock to the area outside of town which has several high end resorts. Other excellent affordable options within Curepipe include rental apartments and condos.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Taxi</strong> - Ask for Curepipe and the driver will know exactly where to go.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - The Motorway M1 between Moka Montagne Ory and Moka City leads to Curepipe.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - From Port Louis Victoria Bus Station, UBS bus takes tourists to Curepipe via Bagatelle.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(746, 15, 62, 1876, '', 'Mauritius', 'BLUE BAY', 'beach-2123440_640.jpg', 'beach-2123440_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">One of the finest spots to enjoy the natural beauty of the island of Mauritius, Blue Bay is one that should definitely feature on his list of must visit places in the country. Here, tourists can experience the virgin beauty of nature as it still stays as one of the most untouched sites throughout. Whereas the lagoons in the other parts have been heavily damaged and fished, Blue Bay is an area which has been listed as a marine park since 1997 and retains much of the charm Mauritius has always been known for. There are about 38 different varieties of corals and 72 species of fish that inhabit this area. Moreover, it is popular as an excellent diving site where all the adventure lovers can experience some adrenaline rush. Tourists can explore the underwater sea life while sitting and chilling on a glass bottom boat and relax. One of the most sought after destinations in Mauritius remains Blue Bay. Famous for its beautiful beaches and crystal clear waters the beach is a great place to go swimming, snorkelling and relaxing.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Accommodations in Blue Bay cater to families and single travellers looking for relaxing vacations but with the tourism industry still developing comfortable hotel rooms often come at steep prices. Facilities built over the last few years offer luxurious amenities like complimentary meals, air conditioning, cable television, and private bathrooms. Simple guesthouses at budget rates are also plentiful.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - On the road to Mahebourg, in the south east of Mauritius, Blue Bay is a must stop by beach.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Taxi</strong> - Blue Bay is at a distance of about 11 kms from Mauritius Airport. There are taxi services available at the airport that take tourists directly to Blue Bay and the journey takes about 15 minutes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around </strong>- Tourists can easily walk from your hotels or villas to the beach since the area is small and has experienced little development which makes Blue Bay unique and serene for ultimate relaxation.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - BLUE BAMBOO&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;, LOCATED AT COASTAL ROAD, POINTE D&#39;ESNY - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSAS AND PIZZA)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(747, 15, 62, 1875, '', 'Mauritius', 'LE MORNE', 'blue-2105706_640.jpg', 'blue-2105706_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">A UNESCO World Heritage Site Le Morne is symbolic of history and identity of Mauritius. &nbsp;Le Morne is a peninsula located towards south western end of the Indian Ocean. The scenic beauty of this location is enchanting. It is also home to a few rare species of plants. Le Morne is an important attraction in Mauritius reflecting the history as well as the incomparable natural beauty of the country. It is located in south western Mauritius and has a great historical significance due to the fact that it was used as a shelter by runaway slaves and maroons through the 18th and 19th centuries. The main highlight of this place is the iconic Le Morne Brabant, which is a looming basaltic rock peak dotted with caves. It is visited by several thousands of tourists every year for its amazing beaches which are known to be the best in Mauritius. Plus there are opportunities for kite surfing, scuba diving, paragliding as well as deep sea fishing much to the delight of all adventure lovers.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Upscale hotels are the most common accommodation option in Le Morne and guests are sure to enjoy benefits like complimentary meals and drinks as well as the best locations on the lagoon along the west side of the rock. Budget accommodations may be harder to find but available inland. The towns of Grange Riviere Noire north of Le Morne host a few wallet friendly options.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Le Morne is at a distance of about 60 kms from Mauritius Airport. There are taxi services available at the airport that take tourists directly to Blue Bay and the journey takes about one hour.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - The best way to explore one of the most famous mountains of Mauritius, Le Morne, is on a guided hike with Yanature. This organisation has an exclusive access to this place.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(748, 16, 59, 1874, '', 'Costa Rica', 'SAN JOSE', 'san-jose-2107471_640.jpg', 'san-jose-2107471_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The city of San Jose is the heart of Costa Rica and home to over half the population that was first attracted to the region&rsquo;s fertile land and pleasant eternal spring climate. Additionally, San Jose offers a complete variety of museums, parks, restaurants and discos. San Jose is a great base for exploring due to the variety of day excursions accessible from the area. Options include world class white water rafting, coffee plantations and day trips to explore the rain forest and volcanoes. San Jose is filled with rich history and culture has an array of restaurants and bars more than anywhere else in the country. San Jose is home to dense culture and history, exquisite architecture, bustling nightlife and friendly locals. Although the city is fairly modern in terms of Latin American cities, as buildings are rarely older than 100 years, there are still plenty of World War II era buildings.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">San Jose and its outlying areas are full of lodging options from budget hostels to luxury hotels. With so many accommodation choices, all needed to do is to pick the price and preferred location and enjoy the stay. For budget backpackers downtown San Jose offers myriad hostels close to nightlife and budget friendly restaurants. Boutique hotels and upscale guesthouses dot the landscape.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The Juan Santamaria International Airport (SJO) was completely renovated in 2010 and is served by major airlines.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Buses from Mexico, El Salvador, Guatemala, Honduras, Nicaragua and Panama both arrive to and leave from San Jose. Unlike in most cities in Latin America, there is no central bus station there are literally dozens of bus terminals in downtown San Jose.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Trains have recently made a comeback in Costa Rica and, after being shut down for many years several routes have been put back into service using second hand equipment brought over from Spain and some very ancient wooden carriages that look like they have been taken from a museum.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around </strong>- San Jose&#39;s public buses can take tourists anywhere in the city for a tiny price. For San Jose taxi trips always make sure that the meter is running at the beginning of ride.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - SAN JOSE - {FAMOUS FOR PICADILLO IS A DISH MADE FROM POTATO WITH BELL PEPPERS, ONIONS, HERBS, SPICES AND SERVED WITH TORTILLAS OR RICE ; HORNED (CHIFRIJO) IS A DISH MADE FROM BEANS, CHICHARRON (PORK), TOMATO, CUCUMBER, GARLIC, CORIANDER, ONION, LEMON JUICE, TORTILLAS, SPICES ; GRANIZADO IS A ICY BEVERAGE CONSISTS OF CRUSHED ICE WITH SWEET MILK, FRUIT OR CHOCOLATE SYRUP ; CASADO IS A MEAL MADE FROM RICE, BLACK BEANS, PLANTAINS, SALAD, TORTILLA AND INCLUIDE CHICKEN, BEEF, PORK OR FISH ;&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - CHELLES, LOCATED AT CALLE 9, SAN JOSE PROVINCE - (FAMOUS FOR GALLO PINTO IS A DISH MADE FROM RICE AND BLACK BEANS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - TAQUERIA EDUARDO, LOCATED AT 3123 WILLIAMSBURG DR., - (FAMOUS FOR TACO IS A DISH MADE FROM WHEAT TORTILLAS, MEAT, VEGETABLES AND CHEESE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - FRESHLY BAKED EATERY, LOCATED AT 152 N 3RD ST., 101 - {FAMOUS FOR CHORIPAN IS A TYPE OF SANDWICH MADE FROM BREAD NAMED (MARRAQUETTA OR BAGUETTE), CHORIZO( PORK SAUSAGE)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - O&#39; LIBANO, LOCATED AT &nbsp;SAN JOSE PROVINCE - (FAMOUS FOR BAKLAVA IS A DESERT MADE FRFOM FILO FILLED WITH CHOPPED NUTS AND SWEETENED WITH SYRUP OR HONEY)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(749, 16, 59, 1873, 'Puntarenas', 'Costa Rica', 'MONTEVERDE', 'bridge-2124896_6401.jpg', 'bridge-2124896_6402.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Monteverde literally meaning green mountains is one of the most interesting and most popular tourist destinations in Costa Rica. There are a number of reserves and activities in this area but is best known for the world famous Monteverde Cloud Forest Reserve that shelters countless wildlife species including jaguars, ocelots and the colourfully feathered magnificent quetzal bird. Monteverde is a natural destination for nature lovers and bird watchers. Considered the second most popular place as a tourist destination in Costa Rica Monteverde is also famous for its nature and wildlife, zip lines and suspension bridges and its fabulous local coffee, ice cream and cheeses. Monteverde has 2000 species of plants, 100 species of mammals and 400 species of birds and conservationists are doing their best to protect this fantastic area. Monteverde also has an impressive open air hummingbird garden, a butterfly farm, a herbarium and the world&rsquo;s third largest insect museum. Monteverde Reserve conserves a lush environment of humid vegetation so rich in wildlife that it has become a base for naturalists from all over the world. The magical forest usually wrapped in fog encourages the growth of mosses and ferns which add to the fairyland feel. Monteverde is a great family destination with tons of activities for adventure lovers and little ones.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Monteverde has a wide range of accommodations from hotels, cabins, rental houses and apartments that will fit any eco tourist&#39;s budget and quality expectations. The Monteverde area offers an eclectic mix of accommodation, from hostels, B&amp;B&rsquo;s and wooden cabins to Costa Rica eco resorts. There are also few options available for shared accommodation.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Both international airports Liberia and San Jose are about 4 hours drive to Monteverde.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - The Pan-American Highway connects San Jose and Liberia to Monteverde.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- Buses to Monteverde leave San Jose from the stop known locally as the old Puntarenas bus stop. There are buses from Nicoya, Santa Cruz, Tamarindo, Flamingo, Playa del Coco, Montezuma, Samara, Hermosa, the Nicaraguan border, and Liberia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - There are several Taxi companies and local bus services are going up and down the hill every 2 hours every day. Many of the activities in the area are in walking distance.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - DE LUCIA, LOCATED AT PUNTARENAS PROVINCE - (&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;FAMOUS FOR TRES LECHES IS A TYPE OF BUTTER CAKE MADE FRROM CAKE BASE WHICH IS SOAKED IN MILK AND CREAM)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - SABOR TICO, LOCATED IN MONTEVERDE - (FAMOUS FOR TAMALE IS A DISH MADE FROM CORN MASA, BANANA LEAVES AND CORN HUSKS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - ORCHID CAFE,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT PUNTARENAS PROVINCE - (FAMOUS FOR PANCAKES AND EGG OMELETTE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - ARRECIFES, LOCATED AT PUNTARENAS PROVINCE - {FAMOUS FOR PATACONES IS A TYPE OF SIDE DISH MADE FROM GREEN (UNRIPE) PLANTAINS}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - POLLOLANDIA,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT 145, PROVINCIA DE GUANACASTE - (FAMOUS FOR FRIED CHICKEN)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(750, 16, 59, 1872, 'Alajuela', 'Costa Rica', 'LA FORTUNA', 'volcano-2124889_6401.jpg', 'volcano-2124889_6402.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">La Fortuna a small city in Alajuela province of Costa Rica attracts hordes of tourists with its many natural attractions and activities volcano hikes, crater lagoons, waterfalls, hot springs, white water rafting, hanging bridges, ziplines, kayaking, caverns, and others. But the main attraction is Arenal Volcano, an active andesitic stratovolcano whose perfect cone towers over the town just 10 kms to the west &nbsp;one of the top 10 most active volcanoes in the world until 2010, when it stopped erupting lava and is now dormant. La Fortuna is considered as one of the preferred destinations by the national and international tourists that visit Costa Rica. From the bird watching, waterfalls and exotic plants, the La Fortuna offers a great diversity of attractions and activities to enjoy. La Fortuna in Costa Rica is a lush destination better known around the world for its natural wonders that combine adventure with nature. &nbsp;The town is centred on beautiful park with colourful gardens and a large church. On the streets surrounding the central park lie many restaurants, hotels, tour operators and shops with more lodging and dining on the road leading to the volcano and Lake Arenal. One of the reasons for La Fortuna&rsquo;s popularity is the availability of excess of activities here.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">La Fortuna being a major tourist hub the options for accommodation is numerous and varying. Staying in La Fortuna is relatively inexpensive when compared to the seaside resorts. Some hotels offer the best views of the smoky mountain as well as guided tours of the National Park. While the hotels along the road between La Fortuna and the National Park tend to be geared toward higher end travellers more budget conscious travellers do have a few choices.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air&nbsp;</strong>- Domestic flights are available with Sansa Airlines from San Jose Airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- Direct buses from San Jose, San Carlos and San Ramon take to La Fortuna. Local bus or taxis plies from Tilaran and Penas Blancas to La Fortuna.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Car </strong>- By car it&rsquo;s a 3 to 4 hours drive from San Jose, but the junctions are not very well marked.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Private Shuttle </strong>- The cost of a private transportation with a Costa Rican driver is not much as compared with the benefit of a direct safe drive from San Jose to Arenal and other destinations.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - CHIFA LA FAMILIA FELIZ, LODATED AT 702, ALAJUELA PROVINCE - (FAMOUS FOR ARROz DHAUFA &nbsp;DISH ITS CONSISTS OF A MIxTURE OF FRIED RIDE WITH ONIONS, EGGS, AND MEAT AND SOy SAUDE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - LA CASCADA, LODATED AT &nbsp;ALAJUELA PROVINCE - (FAMOUS FOR ARROZ CON POLLO IS A DISH MADE FROM RICE, CHICKEN AND VEGETABLES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - SODA VIQUEZ, LODATED AT ALAJUELA PROVINCE - (FAMOUS FOR MILKSHAKES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - CAFETO CHILL OUT, LODATED AT 142, PROVINCIA DE ALAJUELA - (FAMOUS FOR PANCAKES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - SODA ARA, LODATED AT ALAJUELA PROVINCE - (FAMOUS FOR EMPANADAS IS A STUFFED PASTRY ITCDONSIST OF MEAT, CHEESE AND OTHER INGREDIENTS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - I&#39;M HUNGRY, LODATED AT DALLE 468, PROVINCIA DE ALAJUELA - (FAMOUS FOR HAMBURGERS AND HOTDOGS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - MUSMANNI, LODATED AT PROVINCIA DE ALAJUELA - (FAMOUS FOR PASTRIES)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(751, 16, 59, 1871, 'Guanacaste', 'Costa Rica', 'TAMARINDO', 'sunset-1318715_640.jpg', 'sunset-1318715_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Tamarindo an old fishing village in the northern part of the country in the province of Guanacaste &nbsp;is a tourist village that developed many accommodations to suit all budgets, it has a great night and day life and many things to do today. This multi cultural community is the perfect place to enjoy life. Tamarindo has beautiful pristine beaches with clean and clear blue water, wonderful climate and the best view covered with natural surroundings. Tamarindo is known for being the best holiday destination as it joins together a variety of activities, places, hotels and restaurants. The entire town is surrounded with a relaxing atmosphere making it famous and a great place for tourists to visit. Tamarindo Beach is big enough for those seeking for peace and quiet, but for those who want party and noise Tamarindo is the favourite place to rock. Tamarindo is surrounded by leafy forests and deep blue waters that offer travellers a unique mix of nature and nightlife. With warm waters and stable sets accompanying Tamarindo&#39;s golden beaches the town has attracted die hard surfers for years and surf camps are all over as the tanned and toned surfers catching waves off shore.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There is abundance of other hotels and lodgings in Tamarindo and truly is lodging for every budget. Tamarindo has a wealth of accommodation options. Budget travellers favour the area&#39;s hostels and surf camps located a few blocks from the beach. Most upscale hotels and resorts are located beachfront or nearby Langosta. The town also boasts a nice selection of boutique hotels and mid range guest houses.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The easiest and fastest way to reach Tamarindo is to fly into Daniel Oduber Airport in Liberia. They offer several fights a day from all over The United States, Canada and Europe.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - There are several local buses and private shuttle buses from San Jose to Tamarindo such as Grayline and Inter bus that take about 5 to 6 hrs to reach Tamarindo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Car</strong> - Many car rental companies have agencies near Juan Santamaria airport that offer a variety of pick up and drop off options and the drive to Tamarindo is about 4 to 5 hrs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - Tamarindo is a small town to get around on foot. There are several car rental agencies for exploring locations outside of Tamarindo. Tourists can also rent scooters or hail a taxi.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - SODA BUEN COMER, LOCATED AT 152 PROVINCIA DE GUANACASTE - {FAMOUS FOR QUESADILLA IS A FOOD MADE FROM WHEAT TORTILLA, CHEESE, MEAT, SALSA, MUSHROOM, REFRIED BEANS, AVOCADO(FRUIT) AND OTHER VEGETABLES}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - ASIAN FUSION BISTRO, LOCATED AT GUANACASTE PROVINCE - (FAMOUS FOR SALMON ROLLS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - THE SNO SHACK, LOCATED AT GUANACASTE PROVINCE - {FAMOUS FOR PINA COLADA IS A SWEET COCKTAIL MADE FROM COCONUT MILK, AND PINEAPPLE JUICE AND BLENDED WITH ICE}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - SURF SHACK, LOCATED IN TAMARINDO - (FAMOUS FOR VEIGGE BURGER AND MILKSHAKES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - MANDARINA TROPICAL JUICE, LOCATED AT GUANACASTE PROVINCE - (FAMOUS FOR GRANOLA IS A SNACK CONSISTS OF ROLLED OATS, NUTS, HONEY AND SOMETIMES PUFFED RICE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - NOGUI&#39;S, LOCATED IN TAMARINDO - (FAMOUS FOR BEEF TENDERLOIN SANDWICHES)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(752, 19, 60, 1870, 'Budapest', 'Hungary', 'BUDAPEST', 'budapest-138976_640.jpg', 'budapest-138976_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Budapest famous not only for the monuments reflecting its own 1000 year old culture but also for the relics of others who settled here is often described as the Little Paris of Middle Europe. The River Danube, which splits the city in two conservative Buda and cosmopolitan Pest and the Buda Hills make this experienced capital one of the most beautiful cities in Europe. Suburban Buda and its historic castle district offer medieval streets and houses, museums, caves and Roman ruins. The dynamic Pest side boasts the largest parliament building in Europe, riverside walkway, markets, stores and cafe houses. Long hidden behind the iron curtain Budapest is rightfully regaining its reputation as one of the most vibrant capitals of central Europe. Budapest is a city of full of surprises and wonder, with its lively centre, pretty parks, tall church spires and lavish spas. One of the most exciting cities in the world Budapest is full of secrets hidden spots to explore and old favourites to revisit. Budapest is famous for stunning architecture and thermal springs some of which have been used for therapeutic purposes since pre history.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Tourists can book hotels, hostels and pensions at a better price in Budapest as compared to other European cities. Some of the wellness hotels provide thermal water and a historic spa. The most expensive digs are near Castle Hill and dozens of reliable backpacker hostels are mostly across the river in Pest. However, Buda has better air quality due to the closeness of the hills and the forests lying to the west from the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The only international airport in Budapest is the Franz Liszt International Airport. Many big low cost European airline companies fly to Budapest.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Tourists can arrive in Budapest by Rail jet travelling in economy, first or business class all directly from Frankfurt, Vienna, Salzburg, Innsbruck, Zurich and Munich.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - International bus lines arrive at Nepliget station from which tourists can reach the centre in about 15 minutes by travelling on metro. Bus is often the best option to arrive Budapest from another Hungarian city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Major motorways connect Budapest to other cities and neighbouring countries and driving is often the fastest way to reach long distance destinations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - Most of Budapest&#39;s highlights are within easy walking distance of each other and the city centre and have sidewalks and crosswalks for pedestrians. Budapest&#39;s extensive public transit system is generally convenient and easy to use. Tourists can navigate most central areas by metro but a few major destinations are served by buses or trams.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - BUDAPEST - {FAMOUS FOR, GOULASH IS A TYPE OF SOUP MADE FROM MEAT, NOODLES, VEGETABLES, PAPRIKA AND SPICES ; &nbsp;FISHERMAN&#39;S SOUP OR HALASZLE IS A PAPRIKA BASED FISH SOUP MADE FROM CARPFISH, PAPRIKA, VEGETABLES (RED ONIONS, GREEN &nbsp;PEPPERS, TOMATOES) ; FOZELEK IS A SOUP MADE FROM POTATO, PEAS BEANS, LENTILS AND CARROT MIXED WTH FLOUR AND SOUR CREAM ; SOMLOI GALUSKA(SOMLO DUMPLINGSl ) IS A DESERT MADE FROM SPONGE CAKE &nbsp;LAYERED WITH CHOCOLATE CREAM, WALNUT ; PORKOLT IS A MEAT STEW MADE FROM MEAT, PAPRIKA(IS A GROUND SPICE MADE FROM RED AIR-DRIED FRUITS) AND VEGETABLES ; DOBOS TORTE IS A &nbsp;SPONGE CAKE LAYERED WITH CHOCOLATE BUTTERCREAME AND TOPPED WITH CARAMEL &nbsp;; TOLTOTT KAPOSZTA (STUFFED CABBAGE LEAVES) IS A DISH MADE FROM CABBAGE, FILLED WITH PORK AND MIXED IN RICE, AND FLAVOURED WITH PAPRIKA, TEJFOL ; KURTOSKALACS IS A SNACK MADE FROM FLOUR, SUGAR, MILK, BUTTER, EGGS AND YEAST ; TUROS CSUSZA IS A DISH MADE FROM NOODLES AND PASTA ; JOKAI IS A SOUP MADE FROM SOUR CREAM, BEANS, PORK, PARSLEY ROOT AND CARROT}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - BENDO, LOCATED AT WESSELENYI U., 18, 1077 - (FAMOUS FOR BURGERS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - EGGOIST, LOCATED AT &nbsp;HOLLO U., 3, 1075 - (FAMOUS FOR QUESADILLA IS A TYPE OF FLATBREAD MADE FROM TORTILLAS, CHEESE, MEAT, SALSA, MUSHROOMS, BEANS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - FRANKIE&#39;S, LOCATED AT KISS JANOS ALTABORNAGY U., &nbsp;38, 1126 - (FAMOUS FOR COLESLAW &nbsp;IS A SALAD MADE FROM CABBAGE, VINEGAR, VEGETABLE OIL OR MAYONNAISE AND CREAM)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', '');
