(753, 19, 60, 1869, '', 'Hungary', 'SZENTENDRE', 'szentendre-1018324_640.jpg', 'szentendre-1018324_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Szentendre a nice and picturesque town and quite close to Budapest is situated at the Danube bank at the bottom of Pilis Hills. Szentendre has a beautiful Danube bank with narrow cobblestone covered streets and mediterranean atmosphere. Szentendre a popular place among Hungarian and foreign tourists as well is an ideal place for a gathering. A beautiful small area can be found with big trees, small forest at the Danube bank at south part of the city along with a small playground. Szentendre is a very popular place among painters and a group of Hungarian painters are also named after the city. Szentendre was an important settlement even in Roman times and was a favourite camp of Marcus Aurelius. Formerly Szentendre was mainly an agricultural settlement but today houses can be found at the places of former lands and wine yards and some museums managed to keep the tradition of the former agricultural way of life. Szentendre is also highly popular because of its natural conditions. Szentendre is a town of artists and the streets are full of little galleries selling local artworks and there are a number of museums too. The town has a remarkably well preserved Baroque look and even has its own cross that was created to commemorate the survivors of the plague in 1763.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The town is located at about 20 kms towards north of Budapest on Danube bend. Hence, it is ideal for tourists to stay in Budapest as it has lots of options to stay from lodges to hostels and from mid range budget hotels to 5 star luxurious villas. There are also few options available for shared accommodation.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Car</strong> - Route Number 11 Motorway takes tourists from Budapest to Szentendre.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The suburban railway service departing from Batthyany Square takes tourists to Szentendre in about 40 minutes. Trains depart in around every 10 to 15 minutes in high time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Buses depart in the direction of Szentendre and Esztergom from Arpad Bridge coach station and take about 25-30 minutes to arrive.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Boat</strong> - The most delightful way to arrive in Szentendre is by boat. This will take the longest but the trip is well worth it to admire the scenery along the way.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - AL CUOR CONTENTO, LOCATED AT ALKOTMANY U., 5, 2000 - (FAMOUS FOR CARBONARA IS A PASTA DISH MADE FROM EGG, BACON, BLACK PEPPER AND CHEESE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - ADRIA CAFE, LOCATED AT KOSSUTH LAJOS &nbsp;U., 4, 2000 - (FAMOUS FOR HUMMUS IS A &nbsp;LEVANTINE DIP OR SPREAD MADE FROM MASHED CHICKPEAS OR OTHER BEANS, BLENDED WITH TAHINI, OLIVE OIL, LEMON JUICE, AND GARLIC)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - SZENTENDRE - {FAMOUS FOR, KREMES (CREMESCHNITTE) IS A CAKE DESERT MADE FROM PUFF PASTRY, CHANTILLY AND CREAM ; LANGOS IS A TYPE OF DEEP FRIED FLATBREAD MADE FROM FLOUR, YEAST AND IT IS EATEN WITH GARLIC SAUSE, CHEESE, TEJFOL (SOUR CREAM) OR SAUSAGES}</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(754, 19, 60, 1868, '', 'Hungary', 'SZEGED', 'szeged-hungary-699631_640.jpg', 'szeged-hungary-699631_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Szeged is the third largest city of Hungary in Csongrad County and the regional centre of the Southern Great Plain with the University of Szeged being one of the most renowned universities in Hungary. The city is situated near the southern border of Hungary napping on both banks of the Tisza River and possessing an intermediate climate swinging between oceanic and continental and fairly low precipitation. Szeged owes a good share of its charm to the Tisza River which divides the city in two parts. The eastern part of the city known as New Szeged is a spring of calmness full of parks and terraced houses. The river banks offer nice views and shady shelter from the heat. Szeged also known as the city of sunshine happens to excel in producing certain foodstuffs that are Hungarian favourites. It is home to Hungary&rsquo;s most famous salami company and produces some of the country&rsquo;s finest paprika. With its extensive architecture and world famous cooking products, Szeged is one of the most beautiful cities of Hungary.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">From the baroque style to the romantic and modern the town&rsquo;s hotels also have something to shout about. There are lots of hotels and other accommodation in Szeged. There are fairly generic four star establishments with large rooms and nice balconies located just at the main city centre. The rooms in every accommodation are comfortable and equipped with everything needed. At the hotels the staffs is very attentive and help guests with their problems and needs.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest international airport to Szeged is Ferihegy International Airport in Budapest. Szeged also has a small airport which is used for small airplanes or private planes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- The Highway M 5 connects Szeged to Budapest which is about two hours drive from Budapest.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- It takes about 2 to 2 and half hours to travel by train from Budapest Nyugati to Szeged. These trains also stop at Ferihegy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- There are daily frequent buses from Szeged running to surrounding cities including Budapest.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1- SZEGED - {FAMOUS FOR, VANILLEKIPFERL IS A TYPE OF BISCUIT MADE FROM ALMONDS OR NUTS AND VANILLA ; SHLISHKES IS A DISH MADE FROM POTATOES, EGGS, FLOUR AND STREUSEL ; &nbsp;KAISERSCHMARRN IS A TYPE OF PANCAKE MADE FROM FLOUR, EGGS,SUGAR, MILK AND BUTTER ; PALATSCHINKE IS A TYPE OF PANCAKE MADE FROM EGGS, WHEAT FLOUR AND MILK ; SALAMI IS A TYPE OF CURED SAUSAGE CONSISTING OF MEAT(BEEF OR PORK)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - OREG HALASZ VENDEGLO, LOCATED AT ZAMARD UTCA 10., 8600 - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;STRUDEL &nbsp;IS A TYPE OF PASTRY FILLED BY FILO)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(755, 19, 60, 1867, '', 'Hungary', 'SIOFOK', 'lake-balaton-2035921_640.jpg', 'lake-balaton-2035921_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Siofok is a city in the south of Hungary located on the banks of the Balaton Lake. It is also known as Balaton Lake&#39;s Capital and is a popular tourist destination due to its mild climate. The city lays 106 kms from Budapest and has a rich historical tradition. The name as known today has been used starting 1790. In 1552 the village experienced a change of fortunes when it became the basis for the Hungarian Air force and for a fortified army phalanx. Another change of fortunes occurred between 1834 and 1865 when railway lines were laid and the residents were allowed to hold a marketplace in the village. The city became known as a marketplace city. At the end of World War II the city lost its popularity for residence but in 1948 it began to recover and developed into a tourist resort for union members who spurred an improvement of hotels and cabins. Today Siofok is one of the most important tourist centres in Hungary.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Although this small town may not offer a huge selection of places to stay most accommodation blends in perfectly with its charming atmosphere. Choose from several boutique hotels or the more numerous guesthouses and bed and breakfasts. A handful of rental apartments and hostels rounds out the selection. Alternatively, those who want to surround themselves with lush nature can stay at one of the campsites just outside Siofok.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest major airport to Siofok is Budapest Ferenc Liszt International Airport which is at a distance of about 110 kms from Siofok city centre.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Trains to Siofok leave from Deli pelyaudvar railway station in Budapest and the journey takes about an hour and thirty minutes. Trains also run along the coast from Nagykanizsa in the west.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - National highway 7 passing through Siofok connects the city to Budapest and rest of the parts of the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- There are regular busses between major cities in the Transdanube region and Siofok.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Boat</strong> - Most towns around the lake can be accessed by boat and the prices are relatively low, so it is worth to make day trips to Siofok during vacations.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - SIOFOK - {FAMOUS FOR PUNJENA PAPRIKA &nbsp;IS A DISH MADE OF PEPPERS, WITH A MIXTURE OF MEAT, RICE AND EGGS IN TOMATO SAUCE ; RIGO JANCSI IS A TYPE OF CAKE MADE FROM FLOUR, BUTTER, SUGAR, EGGS FILLING WITH CHOCOlATE AND CREAM, APRICOT jAM AND VANILLA ; ROULADEN &nbsp;IS A MEAT DISH CONSISTING OF BACON, ONIONS, MUSTARD AND PICKlES}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - ARANYTOLCSER FAGYLALTKERT ES KAVEZO, LOCATED AT ORGONA U. 6, 8600 - (FAMOUS FOR ICE-CREAM)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - CHAMPION II. PEKSEG, LOCATED IN SIOFOK - (FAMOUS FOR PASTRIES)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(756, 19, 60, 1866, '', 'Hungary', 'LAKE BALATON', 'sailing-boat-1604128_640.jpg', 'sailing-boat-1604128_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Lake Balaton affectionately known as the Hungarian Sea has long been a favourite Hungarian holiday destination. During communism the shallow lake and its surrounding villages served as a meeting point for east and West Germans separated by the Berlin Wall. Here there are beautiful vineyards overlooking the lake, volcanic hills which produce lovely mineralised wines and lots of small family operated cellars. While the lakeside is lined with strands for sun bathing and vendors selling langos and beer, the countryside surrounding the lake is full of rolling grasslands of wild flowers, curved streams and tiny villages with pretty churches, patches of vineyards and views of the glaring lake from many angles. While the quieter north side is characterized by hills covered by a patchwork of grapevines set among fields of lavender and chunks of limestone the south side is mostly flat. The Balaton area produces mostly crisp and sweet smelling white wines though the southern shore is producing an increasing amount of reds.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The cities around Lake Balaton like Balatonfured, Siofok and Keszthely comprises of lots of medium, low budget and luxurious hotels along with lodges, guest houses and rooms on rent. &nbsp;The hotels in these cities provide with consistency in both maintenance and service while smaller locally owned properties are less service oriented.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Lake Balaton is about an hour&#39;s drive from Budapest. National Highway 7 to Siofok is the quickest road to get to the northern shore of Lake Balaton.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Trains from Budapest&#39;s Deli Station run to all main resorts of Lake Balaton.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- Hungary&rsquo;s nationwide Volanbusz bus service offers daily service between Budapest and Balatonfured, Siofok and Keszthely from Pest&rsquo;s Nepliget Station however with frequent stops along the way this can be a time consuming means of travel.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - LAKE BALATON - {FAMOUS FOR, ROAST ZANDER IS A SPICE DISH OF FISH ; BALATON-STYLE FISH SOUP CONTAINS DIFFERENT KINDS OF FISH ARE CARP, CATFISH, SEABREAM OR BROWN BULLHEAD, PAPRIKA, POTATO AND GARLIC ; &nbsp;LANGOS IS A TYPE OF FRIED FLATBREAD MADE FROM FLOUR AND YEAST}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - PARTI CSARDA&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;, LOCATED AT KESZTHELY, PAVILONSOR - (FAMOUS FOR CHEESEBURGER)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(757, 14, 61, 1865, '', 'Maldives', 'MALE', 'maldives-974736_640.jpg', 'maldives-974736_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Male is the capital city of the Maldives and boasts everything a typical capital city should. Occupying the entire islet of Male this city is located at the southern rim of North Male Atoll. Male is in some ways one of the densest countries in the world. A new island Hulhumale which was built between Male and Hulhule is being reclaimed from the sea. Take a trip to the capital city of the Maldives where the residential streets are shaded with trees, forming arches overhead. A stroll around will help discovering historic sites such as the Islamic Centre, the Male Fish Market, Republic Square, Sultan Park, National Museum and more. After a leisurely lunch, stroll around the island gaining insight into the life and livelihood of the residents of the capitol or simply sit down and relax at one of the small parks that dot the capitol to observe the pace of life. Pleasant and pretty, quick and quirky, Male offers an experience to remember, and one not enjoyed anywhere else. A wide variety of shops and markets cater to spending needs while numerous restaurants and cafes offer Maldivian delicacies to tempt the taste buds.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Male is home to numerous guest houses however they are geared towards the local traveller and do not necessarily offer the amenities international tourists expect. It is recommended to indulge a bit on accommodation as the cheap and mid range hotels are usually not up to international standards. The quality of accommodation varies from island to island as do the prices. There is really no such thing as a budget stay in Maldives the degrees of comfort and facilities begin at good and go further up.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The international airport of the country, Male International Airport is located on the island of Hulhule and lies at 1 km distance from the capital Male.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water</strong> - A few private cruises and ships frequent the shores of the country occasionally. Yachts usually steer clear as navigating around the reefs is hazardous and permits are expensive.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around </strong>- Getting around in the Maldives takes three forms boats, air taxis and private yachts. The boats are the Maldivian equivalent of a car while planes and private yachts are mainly reserved for tourists. Public ferries and cargo boats are available for more independent minded and budget conscious travellers.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - MALE - {FAMOUS FOR GARUDIYA IS A FISH DISH BROTH (SAVORY LIQUID MADE OF WATER IN WHICH BONES, MEAT, FISH OR VEGETABLES HAVE BEEN SIMMERED) BASED ON FISH LIKE TUNA AND EATEN WITH STEAMED RICE AND ROSHI ( THE MALDIVIAN CHAPATI) ; MAS HUNI IS A BREAKFAST DISH MADE FROM TUNA(FISH), ONION, COCONUT AND CHILLI ; GULHA IS A PASTRY BALLS THAT ARE STUFFED WITH SMOKED FISH ; KULHI BOAKIBA IS A SPICY FISH CAKE ; BAJIYA IS A PASTRY THAT IS STUFFED WITH FISH, COCONUT AND ONION&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - ZEEBA&#39;S CAFE, LOCATED AT IRAMAA &nbsp;MAGU - (FAMOUS FOR SANDWICHES AND BURGERS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - SEASIDE GRILL MALDIVES, LOCATED AT LOT 10105 DHIGGA MAGU, HULHU MALE - (FAMOUS FOR HOTDOGS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - THE ISLAND BITE, LOCATED AT GURAIDHOO - (FAMOUS FOR FRIED RICE)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(758, 19, 91, 1861, '', 'Netherlands', 'AMSTERDAM', 'amsterdam-2203084_640.jpg', 'amsterdam-2203084_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Amsterdam the capital of the Netherlands is one of the greatest tourist magnets in Europe. A relaxed cosmopolitan atmosphere, exciting museums and the picturesque canal district with its tiny bridges, cafes and townhouses makes Amsterdam a popular destination. Beautiful, sloping architecture, cosy bars and canal lined streets are all central to Amsterdam&#39;s enduring appeal. Historic buildings and arched bridges over striking canals adorn the beautiful city of Amsterdam. Known as one of the greatest small cities in the world, Amsterdam charms visitors with its cool and cosy atmosphere. This capital city of Netherlands and the Venice of the North is the essence of the culturally rich continent of Europe. Every corner of Amsterdam is bustling with architectural masterpieces from ancient museums and art galleries to spectacular theatres. The cycling culture of the city is admirable which is not only a mode of transport but a way of life here. A well planned city, Amsterdam has a canal system that is spread throughout its landscape and a lot of important Amsterdam museums have been built on these canal houses.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Amsterdam boasts hundreds of registered hotels and hostels offering rooms suitable for every traveller&#39;s budget and needs. To stay near the best nightlife and shopping exploring the hotels in the city centre is a good option where rooms range from economical to luxurious. For quick access to museums and galleries check out the budget and mid range hotels in the museum quarter just south of the central district.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Schiphol International Airport is one of the busiest in the world and is situated 15 kms south west of the main city. It is well connected to various cities in the world by regular flights.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Amsterdam enjoys excellent rail connectivity with most other cities in Europe. High speed trains to Amsterdam operate from London, Brussels, Paris, Frankfurt and Berlin. A train journey to this Dutch capital has its benefits as it brings face to face with the scenic countryside.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Using public transport is an economical and hassle free way to reach Amsterdam. There are many international bus services which run daily on this route.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Though the Netherlands has a well maintained and state of the art highway network driving in to Amsterdam might not be the best way to enter the city courtesy the many one way roads and poor parking facilities here.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water </strong>- Amsterdam is an important maritime port of Europe. Taking a cruise is a unique and luxurious way to reach Amsterdam.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around </strong>- The public transport system in Amsterdam is managed by GVB that has a widespread bus network connecting all major spots and tourists attractions in the city. Amsterdam is best explored by bike, foot or public transport. Trains, Ferries and Tram Service are also used to commute from the airport to the main city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - AMSTERDAM - {FAMOUS FOR BITTERBALLEN IS A TYPE OF MEAT BASED SNACK, TYPICALLY CONTAINING A MIXTURE OF BEEF OR VEAL (MINCED), BUTTER, FLOUR, PARSLEY AND PEPPER ; STROOPWAFEL IS A WAFFLE MADE FROM FLOUR, BUTTER, BROWN SUGAR, YEAST, MILK, EGGS, CINNAMON ; CROQUETTE IS A &nbsp;FRIED FOOD ROLL MADE FROM MASHED POTATOES OR GROUND MEAT (VEAL, BEEF, CHICKEN), SHELLFISH, CHEESE, VEGETABLES, AND MIXED WITH BROWN SAUCE AND SOAKED INTO MILK ; OLIEBOL IS A TYPE OF FOOD MADE FROM FLOUR, EGGS, YEAST, MILK, BAKING POWDER, SULTANA, CURRANTS, RAISINS, SUCCADE ; POFFERTJES IS A TYPE OF PANCAKE MADE FROM YEAST AND BUCKWHEAT FLOUR ; ONTBIJTKOEK IS A TYPE OF CAKE MADE FROM RYE, CLOVES, CINNAMON, GINGER, SUCCADE, NUTMEG ; &nbsp;STAMPPOT IS A DISH MADE FROM POTATOES, VEGETABLES OR FRUIT AND SERVED WITH SAUSAGE ; TOMPOUCE IS A TYPE OF PASTRY MADE FROM PUFF PASTRY, ICING, PASTRY CREAM ; OSSENWORST IS A BEEF SAUSAGE MADE FROM OX MEAT ; ERWTENSOEP IS A TYPE OF SOUP MADE FROM PEAS, CELERY OR CELERIAC, ONIONS, LEEKS, CARROTS AND POTATOES, PLUS DIFFERENT CUTS OF PORK}&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - LEEMAN DONER, LOCATED AT VAN WOUSTRAAT 160, 1073 LW - (FAMOUS FOR KEBABS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - BENNY&#39;S, LOCATED AT ALBERT CUYPSTRAAT 177, 1073 BG - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;BUTTER CHICKEN)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - THE LOBBY, LOCATED AT NES 49, 1012 KD - {FAMOUS FOR EGGS BENEDICT IS A SNACK MADE FROM EGGS, MUFFIN, BACON(PORK MEAT), SAUCE}<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n5 - THE BUTCHER, LOCATED AT ALBERT CUYPSTRAAT 129, 1053 BE - (FAMOUS FOR BEEFBURGER)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(759, 19, 91, 1864, '', 'Netherlands', 'LEIDEN', 'leiden-972604_640.jpg', 'leiden-972604_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Leiden was Holland&#39;s first University City and today offers an unbeatable combination of character full architecture, high quality museums and picturesque canals. The events are as diverse as a Rembrandt ice sculpture exhibition and a musical of his life. Leiden is known as the City of Refugees. Throughout history Leiden has given shelter to people who were no longer welcome elsewhere. In the 17th century the population of Leiden grew from just over 20000 to 70000 in a short amount of time. Even in the 20th century no less than three out of four Leiden inhabitants descended from a refugee. The Pilgrims too found a safe harbour in Leiden. At any time Leiden is a refreshing change from the hustle and bustle of Amsterdam. The city&#39;s form is dictated by two types of waterways. There are the defensive canals and moats that encircle the city with the oldest at the centre and the last, a 17th century waterway marking the boundary of the city centre. Through the middle of the city, flowing from east to west is the historical course of the Rhine which marked the northern edge of the Roman Empire. It splits into two arms through the centre and flows out into the North Sea at Katwijk. The spirit of the Golden Age lives on here, a place where Rembrandt was born and inspired so many other influential painters. But even after this era Leiden continued to attract scientists, artists and industry.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">A relatively small city with a big student population, Leiden caters to both long and short stay visitors making their plans on a limited budget. The historical city centre remains the most expensive area, offering rooms in charming old buildings turned into elegant hotels. Just a short walk from this area one can choose from inexpensive lodgings in family-run inns, where cozy rooms come with private parking and free Wi-Fi.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- At Amsterdam and Rotterdam Airport, flights are continually landing from the major cities of neighbouring countries.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Leiden is best reached by train. The journey takes 10 to 15 minutes from The Hague, and 20 minutes from Schiphol Airport, the principal airport in the Netherlands. The journey from Amsterdam takes between 30 to 40 minutes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Two highways around Leiden highway A-4 and A-44 connect Leiden to rest of the cities in Netherlands.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- Leiden train station is a central hub for the local bus network, so if wanting to go anywhere local the best bet is to go there and ask around.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around </strong>- Everything is easily reached on foot and the city is positively charming as a walking pleasure. Alternatively tourists can also rent a bike at the different bike rental shops.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - LEIDEN - {FAMOUS FOR SPECULAAS IS A TYPE OF BISCUIT MADE FROM FLOUR, SUGAR, BUTTER, PEPPER, CINNAMON, GINGER, CLOVES, CARDAMOM, NUTMEG ; VLAAI IS A TYPE OF DESERT MADE FROM YEAST DOUGH, FRUITS, BERRIES ; BERENKLAUW &nbsp;IS A DEEP-FRIED FAST FOOD SNACK &nbsp;IT CONSISTS OF A SLICED MEATBALL AND FRIED IN ONION WITH PEANUT SAUCE ; KAASSOUFFLE IS A SNACK OF MELTED CHEESE INSIDE A THIN DOUGH-BASED WRAP WHICH HAS BEEN BREADED AND THEN DEEP-FRIED ; PEPERNOOT IS A TYPE OF CANDY MADE FROM FLOUR SUGAR ANISEED CINNAMON CLOVES}<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - DE DRIE GRAEFJES, LOCATED AT ROKIN 128, 1012 LC - {FAMOUS FOR RED VELVET CAKE IS A CAKE MADE FROM FLOUR, BUTTER, SUGAR, BUTTERMILK, COCOA POWDER, OR CREAM CHEESE, BEETROOT OR RED FOOD FOR COLORING}&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - PANNENKOEKENHUYS OUDT LEYDEN B.V., LOCATED AT STEENSTRAAT 49, 2312 BV - (FAMOUS FOR APPLE STRUDEL IS A TYPE OF PASTRY MADE FROM FLOUR, OIL OR BUTTER, APPLES)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - BANKETBAKKERIJ EN LUNCHROOM SNIJERS, LOCATED AT BOTERMARKT 15, 2311 EM - (FAMOUS FOR CAKES AND FRUIT JUICES)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(760, 19, 91, 1864, '', 'Netherlands', 'ROTTERDAM', 'skyline-1601187_640.jpg', 'skyline-1601187_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The city of Rotterdam is located in the South Holland province. It is a welcoming city with a plethora of museums, bars and restaurants to entertain visitors and residents. Rotterdam is a vibrant city known for its architecture, art and edginess and is fast becoming a must see European destination. Rotterdam makes a great alternative for visitors wanting to avoid the more tourist trodden Amsterdam and although this is true, Rotterdam is a truly exciting destination in its own right. Rotterdam is the second largest city in the Netherlands and forms the southern part of the Randstad, the 6th largest metropolitan area in Europe. Rotterdam is home to Europe&rsquo;s biggest port only Shanghai&rsquo;s is bigger than this. It is a major transportation hub for the whole of Northern and Central Europe. Rotterdam is divided into a northern and a southern part by the Nieuwe Maas River. The city centre is located on the northern bank of the Nieuwe Maas although recent urban development has extended the centre to parts of southern Rotterdam known as the Head of South.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Rotterdam offers comfortable lodgings for every budget from neat little rooms in youth hostels to luxurious suites in boutique hotels. The city&#39;s centrally located establishments offer five star service and easy access to outstanding museums, theatres, restaurants and bars. The well connected area near the central train station draws backpackers with its good value hostels many of which offer bicycles for rent. There are also riverfront guesthouses which provide private parking, laundry facilities and secure luggage storage.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The Hague airport located 6 kms north of the city centre has several regional and low cost airlines flying in and out of Rotterdam.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - High speed international trains whizz into Rotterdam&rsquo;s futuristic Central station ten times a day. And with hundreds of train connections to other Dutch cities reaching Rotterdam is easy from any corner in the Netherlands.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water</strong> - Tourists can take the ferry from the United Kingdom. P&amp;O Ferries sail from Hull to Rotterdam Euro port which is in the centre of the city and Stena Line sails from Harwich to Hoek van.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - From Amsterdam take the Highway A-4 south to Hague, change to the Highway A-13 to Rotterdam. From Utrecht take the Highway A-12 and change to the Highway A-20 just after Gouda.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Bus service operates between Rotterdam and many cities across Europe. Buses arrive and depart at the Rotterdam Central Station. Tickets can be purchased online or from the office.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - The most obvious way of getting around any Dutch city is by bike of course but Rotterdam also offers many other forms of public transport such as the bus metro and even a water taxi.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - ROTTERDAM - {FAMOUS FOR KAPSALON IS A TYPE OF FAST FOOD MADE FROM FRENCH FRIES, MEAT (D&ouml;NER OR SHAWARMA), GOUDA CHEESE, SALAD VEGETABLES AND &nbsp;SERVED WITH GARLIC SAUCE AND SAMBAL ; FRIKANDEL IS A SNACK MADE FROM MINCED MEAT ; KRENTENBOLLEN OR CURRANT BUN &nbsp;IS A SWEET BUN THAT CONTAINS CURRANTS OR RAISINS ; HOLLANDSE NIEUWE HARING IS A FISH DISH &nbsp;SERVED WITH CHOPPED ONIONS, AND EATEN WITH BREAD} &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - FLAT WHITE, LOCATED AT COOLSINGEL 83, 3012 AD - (FAMOUS FOR PASTRIES AND COFFEE)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - EETCAFE PENNY PEAN, LOCATED AT MEENT 39-A, 3011 JC - (FAMOUS FOR PEA SOUP)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - MULTIFOOD CORNER, LOCATED AT COOLSINGEL 87A, 3012 AE - (FAMOUS FOR SANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(761, 19, 91, 1863, '', 'Netherlands', 'BREDA', 'breda-1894224_640.jpg', 'breda-1894224_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Breda is a wonderful fun loving city in the southern part of Netherlands. Breda is it the main city of Nassau in Holland, boasting many imposing monuments. Between 1403 and 1568, the ancestors of royal family converted Breda to a beautiful city with richly decorated buildings. Even today these architectural pearls still manage to impress. Breda is a city in the west of the province North Brabant of the Netherlands and has over 170000 inhabitants. It is a very cosy and social city, partly due to the large number of students that live in the city. In the historical city centre tourists will find lots of interesting architecture and cultural delights. For those individuals who may be major history enthusiasts, this would be the ideal destination. From Breda&rsquo;s stunning castles to other major architectural monuments within the town, there are tons of interesting and fun activities to participate in and sites to see in the lovely little medieval town. The local generally consider Breda as the best in history, art and shopping and is a hub for culture in the Netherlands. In comparison to the majority of other major cities that may offer boat tours Breda possesses a unique advantage they offer a calm atmosphere that to be enjoyed leisurely.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">As befitting a busy regional capital Breda boasts lodging options that range from low cost hostels for budget minded travellers, to stylish boutique hotels catering to those who wish to indulge themselves. Breda is as a popular weekend destination throughout the year so book in advance if want a spacious room near the city centre. Spontaneous travellers can check out the areas just outside the central district where many guesthouses offer free parking and bicycles for rent.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest major airport is Eindhoven Airport. This airport has international and domestic flights from Eindhoven and is 51 kms from the centre of Breda.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Highway A-2 and A-27 which will take tourist from Amsterdam to Breda and it is only about 60 kms from Rotterdam through highway A-16.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - NS Dutch Railways operates trains operate between Breda and most cities in the Netherlands and neighbouring countries.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water</strong> - P&amp;O Ferries operates overnight ferry service between Hull, England and Rotterdam, the nearest port to Breda and the journey takes 12 hours.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - The main form of transport in Breda is the local buses. As with most public transport in the Netherlands, the buses in Breda are generally clean and reliable. Probably the easiest form of transport in Breda is the bicycle.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1- BREDA - {FAMOUS FOR KIBBELING IS A SNACK CONSISTING OF FRIED FISH, AND SERVED WITH A MAYONNAISE BASED GARLIC OR TARTAR SAUCE ; UITSMIJTER IS A TYPE OF SANDWICH MADE FROM &nbsp;BREAD, FRIED IN BUTTER,COVERED WITH HAM AND FRIED EGG ; ZEEUWSE BOLUS IS A TYPE OF SWEET PASTRY MADE FROM &nbsp;DOUGH, TREACLE, CINNAMON ; METWORST IS A TYPE OF SAUSAGE &nbsp;MADE FROM RAW MINCED PORK} &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(762, 19, 91, 1862, '', 'Netherlands', 'ARNHEM', 'netherlands-2224843_640.jpg', 'netherlands-2224843_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">As the capital of Gelderland, Arnhem has a rich and interesting history, part of which can be discovered in a number of monumental buildings. Arnhem is surrounded by green landscapes with the Veluwe on one side and the water meadows on the other. Arnhem has been among the top 10 best shopping cities in Holland for years now. A visit to Arnhem is easily combined with one of the many top attractions. Arnhem is known mostly for its John Frost Bridge, which the British tried to secure during World War II. Arnhem is probably best known for the battle conducted here in 1944 and immortalised in the film &lsquo;A Bridge Too Far&rsquo; but Arnhem today is a peaceful medium sized city that sits on the banks of the Rhine. Many who go to Arnhem do so for its historical museums, war monuments, museum of modern art and the Burgers&#39; zoo. Although mostly known for its recent history Arnhem is an interesting and friendly city. They have restaurants that specialize in cuisines from different parts of the world as well as local and traditional Dutch food and recipes.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Although many visitors to Arnhem end up choosing a centrally located hotel near the main train station, tourists can find plenty of equally comfortable rooms farther away from this busy part of town. For easy access to the surrounding countryside check out the guest houses and self catering apartments on the outskirts of town, where one can get a quiet night&#39;s sleep.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Schiphol airport in Amsterdam is about 110 kms to the northwest of Arnhem. Schiphol airport gets served by most major carriers per day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Highway A-12, A-50 and A-325 connect Arnhem to various cities in Netherlands like The Hague, Zwolle, Nijmegen, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- The Arnhem railway station is the main station of Arnhem and at present has lot of passengers that use the station per day this makes it the 9th busiest station in the Netherlands.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- Tourists can reach Arnhem by bus from cities as Apeldoorn, Nijmegen and Wageningen. The bus station of Arnhem is located next to the train station in the city centre.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around </strong>- The local trolley buses and very good and are linked up well so that tourists can easily get to the destination. The bus station is conveniently located next to the train station in the town centre. &nbsp;A bicycle is an ideal way to get around town and taxis are also available.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - ARNHEM - {FAMOUS FOR ATJAR IS A TYPE OF SALAD MADE FROM VEGETABLES LIKE (CUCUMBER, CARROTS, CABBAGE), ONION, CHILI AND YARDLONG BEANS, VINEGAR, PEANUTS ; SPEKKOEK IS A TYPE OF CAKE MADE FROM EGG YOLKS, BUTTER, SUGAR, CINNAMON, CLOVE, MACE AND ANISE ; HACHEE IS A TYPE OF STEW MADE FROM MEAT, FISH OR POULTRY, VEGETABLES AND SERVED WITH RICE ; ROOKWORST IS A SAUSAGE MADE FROM &nbsp;PORK AND SPICES ;&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(763, 19, 91, 1861, '', 'Netherlands', 'TEXEL', 'lighthouse-1111176_640.jpg', 'lighthouse-1111176_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">With its 30 kms of sandy beaches Texel Island is a paradise for beach lovers. Texel has much more to offer, however seven villages each one pretty as a picture and unique natural scenery and is within easy and quick reach. On Texel there&#39;s room enough for large nature areas a significant farming culture and seven small villages. In an area roughly the same size as the capital, there are less than 14000 inhabitants not including the sheep. Den Burg the biggest of the villages is both charming and vibrant boasting plenty of interesting local shops and even a cute little cinema. The island is renowned for its bird watching opportunities and it&#39;s fascinating to discover that the island is a vital stop off point for migrating birds from across the world. From unwinding in nature all the way through to sporting activities like cycling, walking or even parachuting. Texel is a wonderful destination throughout the year for a weekend away or a longer holiday. The bright red lighthouse is located off one of the island&rsquo;s widest beaches on northern Texel. For the perfect outing, combine a day at the beach with a tour of the lighthouse. Texel consists of a total of 7 villages with a plethora of small towns being seen. There is also a sand bar that is uninhabited dubbed Noorderhaaks.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">In terms of accommodation, Texel has something to offer for every taste. Texel is host to a wide range of hotels tourists can choose from a selection of 2 star hotels or luxury 4 star hotels close to the beach or near the forest. There are also holiday homes available ranging from static caravans, villas and modern apartments. There are also camp sites in Texel with a laundrette, playing field, recreational programme or restaurant. There is also a wide choice of group accommodation all of which are easily accessible and equipped with all modern conveniences.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Texel International Airport is a modern airport with a grass landing strip situated in Eierland. Texel has been dubbed the friendliest airfield in the Netherlands and a visit to Texel Airfield is a pleasant outing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water</strong> - Tourists can moor a boat overnight in Waddenhaven Texel in Oudeschild. This modern marina with many facilities has both large and small cubicles available. Where only a few boats used to dock at Texel the past 50 years have seen aquatic sports expand enormously.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Den Helder can be reached by train. The ride to Den Helder station takes 1 hour and 15 minutes from Amsterdam and 2 hours from Rotterdam. Teso operates a 30 minutes ferry trip from Den Helder to Texel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - The island is best experienced by bicycle, in the summer. There are many places to hire bikes on the island. Public transport busses run each hour to each village and connect to the hourly ferry services.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - TEXEL - {FAMOUS FOR BAMI GORENG IS &nbsp;A DISH MADE FROM FRIED NOODLES WITH CHICKEN, MEAT OR PRAWN ; SATE IS A DISH MADE FROM MEAT OF (CHICKEN, PORK, BEEF) AND SERVED WITH PEANUT SAUCE ; SHAKSHOUKA IS A DISH OF EGGS POACHED IN A TOMATO SAUCE, CHILI PEPPERS, ONIONS AND SPICED WITH CUMIN ; BANKETLETTER IS A PASTRY MADE FROM A MIXTURE OF FLOUR, EGGS AND BUTTER FILLED WITH ALMOND PASTE, DUSTED WITH SUGAR}<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - EL TORO, LOCATED AT NIKADEL 1, 1796 DE KOOG - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN WRAP AND LASAGNE IS A TYPE OF PASTA &nbsp;MADE FROM &nbsp;DURUM WHEAT)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(764, 19, 92, 1860, '', 'Poland', 'WARSAW', 'poland-2254978_640.jpg', 'poland-2254978_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Warsaw is the capital of Poland and is a part of the Mazovia plane. The city is an amalgamation of the old and the new the traditional and the modern in terms of its architecture. Interestingly it is said that Warsaw together with Paris, Frankfurt, London and Barcelona has the greatest number of skyscrapers in the European Union. Warsaw is a city that is full of surprises. It contains nearly everything under the sun sparkling skylines, tall skyscrapers and bustling streets exist right alongside peaceful green lawns and gardens, old palaces and Gothic architecture. Tourists flock here in vast numbers to see the Jablonowski Palace, Old Town market square, etc. The Monument of The Warsaw Mermaid is the most popular symbol of the city. Warsaw is steeped in culture and history as is evident in their places of attraction including galleries, palaces and museums. Warsaw is actually a multi cultural city. However Catholicism is the most dominant religion here followed by the Protestants.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Warsaw gives you plenty of options to choose from when it comes to hotels. Many centrally located hotels in Warsaw cater mostly to business travellers which make them much too expensive for backpackers and other visitors on a limited budget. Although hostels may seem like the only affordable option at the height of the season tourists can find less expensive lodgings in mid range hotels on the outskirts of town.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Warsaw is quite easy to get to as it has two airports the Chopin Airport and Warsaw Modlin Airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Warszaw Centralna, Warszawa Zachodnia and Warszawa Wschodnia are the 3 huge railway stations in Warsaw. All three bring in both international as well as domestic trains so it&#39;s quite easy to get to this city by train.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Dworzec PKS Warszawa Zachodnia is the bus station in Warsaw. It receives international as well as national connections. There are also private buses from nearby cities that can get tourists to Warsaw.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - Trams, buses and the metro are the most popular choices for getting around Warsaw.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1- WARSAW - {FAMOUS FOR BARSZCZ (OR BORSCHT) IS A TYPE OF SOUP MADE FROM BEETROOT&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; ; KASZA IS A &nbsp;PORRIDGE MADE FROM CEREAL (BUCKWHEAT, WHEAT, BARLEY, OATS, MILLET OR RYE) AND BOILED IN MILK OR WATER ; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;ZUPA GRZYBOWA (MUSHROOM SOUP) IS A TYPE OF SOUP MADE FROM ROUX, CREAM OR MILK, MUSHROOMS ; GOLABKI IS A SNACK ROLL MADE FROM CABBAGE, PORK, BEEF, ONIONS, RICE ; PIEROGI IS A DESERT MADE FROM &nbsp;FLOUR, EGGS, WATER ; SERNIK IS A TYPE OF DESERT MADE FROM CHEESE, PIE CRUST (GRAHAM CRACKER CRUST, PASTRY, OR SPONGE CAKE), SUGAR ; SEKACZ IS A TYPE OF CAKE MADE FROM BUTTER, EGG, FLOUR, SUGAR, AND CREAM} &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - KROWARZYWA, LOCATED AT HOZA 29/31 - (FAMOUS FOR BEEFBURGER)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(765, 19, 92, 1859, '', 'Poland', 'KRAKOW', 'poland-1449357_640.jpg', 'poland-1449357_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Krakow is probably the most beautiful and fascinating city in Poland. The attraction is not just the splendid architecture and the treasures of art, the reminders of the times when Krakow was a royal capital city but also the unique ambience of the former Jewish district and the masterpieces of Polish Art Nouveau. However old and beautiful it is, Krakow is not limited to its monuments and museums. Thanks to an amazing density and variety of bars, pubs, clubs and restaurants, Krakow sparkles with life. One of Poland&#39;s oldest cities Krakow sits at the foot of the Carpathian Mountains its historical town centre nestled on the left bank of the Vistula River. Home to over a million people the city features 18 distinct boroughs each claiming considerable autonomy and boasting its own particular character. Krakow&#39;s old town a World Heritage Site represents the historical heart of the city and contains its most significant architectural treasures. Architecture is all apparent throughout and is a brilliant combination of fragments of the present and the golden past. The cityscape will strongly remind of Budapest and a little bit of Prague to the tourists because of the essence of European cities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Krakow ranks among one of Europe&#39;s increasingly popular tourist destinations which is reflected in the rising costs of comfortable lodgings. The best hotels are concentrated in and around the historical old town, where five star luxuries comes at a very steep price. If the trip involves a tight budget avoid the central district and check out mid range hotels and economical hostels in one of the outlying neighbourhoods.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- There are many flights that fly to Krakow though they generally stop on Warsaw or European cities like Munich, London, Amsterdam, Madrid, Prague or Berlin.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- One can easily board express train from Warsaw to Karkow Glowny the station located in old town. The train takes 3 hours for a one way journey.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- To get to Krakow one can catch as bus from Warsaw bus depot to Krakow. The bus journey takes 10 hrs and has numerous stops in between. The bus journey from Slovakia to Krakow is faster and cheaper than by train.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- The A4 motorway has been completed from the German border to Krakow. This makes travel from the west fairly easy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - Getting around in Krakow is pretty easy. There is no subway in Krakow and bus lines are operated by municipal company. Taxis/cabs are plentiful and relatively inexpensive in Krakow within the city boundaries.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1- KRAKOW - {FAMOUS FOR PLACKI ZIEMNIACZANE IS A TYPE OF PANCAKE MADE FROM POTATOES, FLOUR, EGG AND &nbsp;SERVED WITH &nbsp;BUNDZ (SHEEP&#39;S MILK CHEESE) AND SOUR CREAM (MIXED WITH YOGURT) ; SZARLOTKA IS A TYPE OF DESERT MADE FROM BREAD, SPONGE CAKE, FRUIT PUREE OR CUSTARD ; NAPOLEONKA (KREM&oacute;WKA) IS A PIE DESERT MADE FROM &nbsp;PUFF PASTRY FILLED WITH CREAM ; KAPUSNIAK OR KWASNICA IS A SOUO MADE FROM STOCK (FISH, MUSHROOM, OR PORK FAT), VEGETABLES ; MAKOWIEC IS A PASTRY MADE FROM FLOUR, SUGAR, EGG YOLK, MILK OR SOUR CREAM, BUTTER, POPPY SEEDS OR CHESTNUTS}&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - MEAT AND GO, LOCATED AT DOLNYCH MłYN&oacute;W 10 - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;BEEF SANDWICH)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - WALENTY KANIA, LOCATED AT JAKUBA 4 - (FAMOUS FOR OFFAL IS A SPICY STEW MADE FROM BEEF TRIPE)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n4 - PAN KUMPIR, LOCATED AT SWIETEGO WAWRZYNCA 16 - (FAMOUS FOR BAKED POTATO)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n5 - KIELBASKI POD HALA TARGOWA,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT GRZEGORZECKA 14 - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;KIELBASA IS A TYPE OF SAUSAGE MADE FROM MEATS)</strong></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', '');
INSERT INTO `city` (`id`, `continent_id`, `country_id`, `state_id`, `state_name`, `country_name`, `ci_name`, `main_image`, `main_image1`, `description`, `accomdation`, `transportation`, `eatable`, `experience_type_id`) VALUES
(766, 19, 92, 1858, '', 'Poland', 'GDANSK', 'gdansk-2110252_640.jpg', 'gdansk-2110252_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Gdansk is a 1000 year old port city on the Baltic coast of Poland which together with the city of Gdynia and the town of Sopot makes up the metropolitan area Trojmiasto, the Tricity. Home to the Westerplatte where World War II broke out in 1939 Gdansk was mostly destroyed during the war but there are still many impressive sights. Wander through cobblestone streets and mazes of red brick buildings to discover the Upland Gate St. Mary&rsquo;s Church the medieval Gdansk Crane or the stunning facade of the Great Arsenal. Explore treasures of Baltic Gold at the Amber Museum or collections of paintings, fabrics and furniture at the National Museum housed in a former Franciscan monastery. Relax at a beer garden or restaurant and take in the beautiful coastline. Make a way to Gdynia home of the Polish navy to feast on seafood or a visit to a floating museum in the form of two ships Dar Pomorza and Blyskawica. Gdansk may well be located on the coast of Poland but the architecture and atmosphere of this portside city remains so otherworldly, it might as well be located in a country all of its own.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The suburbs of Gdansk boast plenty of affordable hotels and hostels offering inexpensive rooms even at the height of the season. Easily accessible by train, neighbouring Sopot provides additional sleeping options, including good value guesthouses and mid range hotels located mere minutes from the Baltic Sea. If preferring to stay in Gdansk itself, explore the city&#39;s self catering apartments with free Wi-Fi and cable TV. Alternatively one can check out the upscale old town hotels, many of which offer discounted rates on the weekends.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Gdansk&rsquo;s local airport is Port Lotniczy Gdansk Trojmiasto about 8 kms from the city centre and connected to most major European capitals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail </strong>- Gdansk Glowny, virtually next door to Gdansk&rsquo;s Old Town, is the city&rsquo;s main train station. Domestic and international trains arrive from across Poland and its neighbouring countries virtually every hour.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- Regular buses from the rest of the country, and from abroad, arrive at Gdansk, terminating at the Dworzec PKS, the central bus station. The station&rsquo;s conveniently located, almost in the heart of the city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water </strong>- Gdansk&rsquo;s New Port is the main landing ground for ferries to and from the city. Gdansk has daily ferry connections to the Swedish port of Nynashamn there&rsquo;s a ferry going to and from Gdansk every day. There is also a small port at Gdynia, which is linked by ferry to Karlskrona.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Gdansk lies on three of Poland&rsquo;s major highways the E-75 from the south, the E-28 from the west and the E-77 from the east. Road conditions are good on the highways, but secondary roads tend to be badly maintained.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around </strong>- Getting around Gdansk should not be a problem for anyone the city has ample transport facilities, ranging from cab on call services and car rentals to extensive bus, tram and commuter train networks.</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>GDANSK - {FAMOUS FOR KASZANKA IS A TYPE OF BLOOD SAUSAGE MADE FROM &nbsp;PORK, PIG&#39;S BLOOD, PIG OFFAL, KASZA, ONIONS, BLACK PEPPER, MARJORAM ; &nbsp;ZAPIEKANKA IS A TYPE OF SANDWICH MADE FROM BAGUETTE(BREAD), MUSHROOMS, CHEESE AND TOMATO KETCHUP ; BIGOS IS A TYPE OF STEW MADE FROM VARIOUS MEATS ; RACUCHY OR RACUSZKI IS A TYPE OF SWEET PANCAKE MADE FROM &nbsp;FLOUR, MILK, EGGS, SUGAR ; FAWORKI IS A SWEET PASTRY MADE FROM DOUGH, POWDERED SUGAR}</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(767, 19, 92, 1857, '', 'Poland', 'ZAKOPANE', 'cottage-484521_640.jpg', 'cottage-484521_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Originally a 17th century forestry settlement Zakopane has been a centre for Polish intellectuals for the past century. This lovely town is also Poland&#39;s best known ski centre. There are seven ski areas around Zakopane offering more than 50 lifts between them, but most are short drag lifts, either running parallel or not connected to one another. Many are also privately owned lifts requiring separate tickets. The region&#39;s largest town is Zakopane, Poland&#39;s premier mountain resort and a popular holiday destination in both winter and summer. The charming town has a laid back fairytale atmosphere, the steep streets lined with traditional wooden cottages made from roughly cut logs and the Zakopane style architecture featuring delicately carved patterns and intricate woodwork decoration. The heart of Zakopane town is a pedestrian mall lined with restaurants, cafes and shops. The region is popular for outdoor activities and one of the more popular holiday attractions is the trip to the exquisite glacial lake, Morskie Oko. The area has good facilities and is known for its fascinating highland folklore and culture and many of the inhabitants wear colourful traditional dress.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Zakopane is a hotel paradise. There are still not enough hotels, hostels, private guest houses and pensions in Zakopane to meet the demand in the high summer season in December January and in February. &nbsp;Many locals rent simply furnished rooms in private houses, providing another low cost alternative for travellers with a limited budget. The best Zakopane hotels and hostels are booked out almost for the whole year and it is thus advisable to plan your stay in Zakopane in advance. In winter it becomes the winter capital of Poland and the number of visitors increases.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Krakow 100 kms is the closest airport in Poland, the drive to Zakopane can take anything from two to four hours depending on the traffic.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- There are around five trains every day from Krakow. It takes three and a half hours and stops at many small towns along the way.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- Several companies ride between Krakow and Zakopane, two biggest are Maxbus and Majer Bus. The journey takes at least two hours fifteen minutes, sometimes more. There is also direct bus from Budapest by Euro Busways.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Zakopianka from Krakow road number 7 to Rabka and then follow route 47 to Zakopane. It takes around one and a half hour, but depends on traffic. Traffic jams on summer weekends are legendary.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around </strong>- The PKS local buses run according to schedule. There is large number of privately owned vans called mini bus. Most have fixed routes and rates and no schedule. Private taxis are also available.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - PODKOWA GOSPODA, LOCATED AT NOWOTARSKA 7 - (FAMOUS FOR POTATO PANCAKES WITH A VEGETABLE SAUCE)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - U STAREGO S.C. CISZEK S., LOCATED AT OSWALDA BALZERA 16B - (FAMOUS FOR GARLIC SOUP, PORKBURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - ZAKOPANE - {FAMOUS FOR PACZKI IS A TYPE OF PASTRY DOUGH, GRAIN ALCOHOL, ICING CONFITURE, POWDERED SUGAR, DRIED ORANGE ZEST ; KOTLET SCHABOWY IS A FOOD MADE FROM PORK OR CHICKEN, EGGS, LARD, SPICES, BREADCRUMBS, FLOUR ; KOTLETY MIELONE ARE MEATBALLS OF MINCED MEAT}</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(769, 19, 92, 1856, 'Swietokrzyskie', 'Poland', 'KIELCE', 'kielce-1549539_1920.jpg', 'kielce-1549539_19201.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\nKielce is located in the middle of the Swietokrzyskie Mountains also known as the Holy Cross Mountains on the banks of Silnica River in the northern part of the historical Polish province of Lesser Poland. It was once an important centre of limestone mining with sandstone and marble from nearby quarries and is now a centre of trade and commerce with factories such as spark plug and bearing makers, a paper mill and chemical industries. In the nearby mountains copper, lead and iron ores have been mined since the Middle Ages and the first technical college in Poland was set up by Stanislaw Staszic a politician and scientist called the Mining Academy. The Cathedral of the Assumption opposite the castle was once a Romanesque church but was transformed into a Baroque place of worship in the 17th century. As well as being the economic, cultural and educational centre of the region the scenically located city of Kielce is an attractive spot for people wanting to enjoy plenty of fresh air. The city also has many green areas where tourists can relax and play and there are even a number of walking routes. Kielce gives an opportunity to rediscover nature for there are five nature reserves within the city&rsquo;s suburban area.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There is full range of accommodation in Kielce from most luxurious five star hotels with up to date and modern amenities to guest house or boarding house and rooms or apartments at very reasonable prices. To stay in a more rural location there are a number of Agro styles of accommodation places on farms and in the countryside plus there may be camp sites nearby.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - At present, air services are only available to the residents of Kielce at Kielce-Maslow Airport, built in 1937, a civilian airport located in nearby Maslow. There is an international airport in the near town of Krakow but more flights go from Warsaw Frederic Chopin Airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Kielce is very easy to reach by train, as it is on the main line between Krakow and Warsaw.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - To travel to Kielce by bus is probably a better option, as the train makes a rather long detour eastward.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around </strong>- There are city buses that connect almost all places of importance within the municipality of Kielce. There are minibuses to villages and small towns in the surroundings.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>KIELCE - {FAMOUS FOR ROSOL IS A SOUP MADE FROM CHICKEN AND NOODLE ; KOPYTKA IS A TYPE OF DUMPLING MADE FROM POTATOES, FLOUR, CHEESE, FRIED BACON AND ONION ; KUTIA IS A DISH MADE FROM WHEATBERRIES, POPPY SEEDS, HONEY, NUTS AND RAISINS ; KISSEL IS A TYPE OF DESERT MADE FROM BERRIES JUICE, ARROWROOT, CORNSTARCH ; &nbsp;NALESNIKI IS A TYPE OF PANCAKE MADE FROM &nbsp;EGGS, MILK AND BUTTER}&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(770, 16, 43, 1525, 'California', 'U.S.A', 'SAN FRANCISCO', 'san-francisco-1633203_640.jpg', 'san-francisco-1633203_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">San Francisco is the fourth most populous city in California, which is the showpiece of the Bay Area, known for its political communities and diverse culture. The city is also known for its hilly terrain, scenic beauty and world class finest restaurants. San Francisco one of the most important cities on the West Coast and all of the United States has been a major tourist destination since 1960 because of its wide array of attractions, fantastic views of the San Francisco Bay and brilliant summer weather. The vibrant and energetic city holds a plethora of activities and attractions to keep tourists busy throughout the stay. It&#39;s a favourite destination especially during the summers, due to its cool temperatures. The city has a great mixture of cultures and is not short on entertainment options either. San Francisco&#39;s most iconic landmark is perhaps the Golden Gate Bridge, covering the width of the San Francisco Bay and offering some fine vistas. Cruises on the Bay are also a famous activity that one shouldn&#39;t miss out. San Fran as it is fondly called is also a paradise for shoppers with several streets of international and local boutiques and the largest Chinatown outside Asia. And as the sun sets, the city wakes up once again to head out for the night to its brilliant offerings of nightclubs and bars. San Francisco is a top holiday destination featuring scenic beauty and great ethnic and cultural diversity. San Francisco is known for sightseeing, nature, museums, parks and historic sites.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">One has so many choices of hotels to pick from when it comes to selecting the hotel to stay at in San Francisco. There are many areas to live in while visiting San Francisco. The options of hotels and dorms in the city are many. There are many other neighbourhoods in the city which will cater to different needs of different visitors.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The San Francisco International is one of the biggest and busiest airports of the world. It connects the city to countries and cities all over the world and in the United States.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - San Francisco is very well connected via rail. There are mainly three railway service providers Amtrak, Caltrain and the regional Bay Area Rapid Transit.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - The city is served by various private bus companies which have their own terminals, so a central common terminal is absent. Greyhound is a company which covers the most destinations to and from San Francisco.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Tourists can get into San Francisco through four major highways, the US-101 from the south and north, the Interstate 280 also from the South and the Interstate 80 from the east.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water</strong> - San Francisco is regularly docked at by international cruise liners and yachts. Domestically it can be approached from various locations on East Bay, Marin County and Solano County.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around </strong>- San Francisco has an extensive network of public transport. The San Francisco Municipal Railway runs a light rail subway system, the Muni Metro and a large network of public buses. It&#39;s famous street car and cable car lines mostly serve as tourist attractions today. Taxis, like everywhere else in the US, also operate extensively.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - ZAM ZAM, LOCATED AT 1633 HAIGHT ST - (FAMOUS FOR MARTINI IS A COCKTAIL MADE WITH GIN AND VERMOUTH, AND GARNISHED WITH AN OLIVE OR A LEMON)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - GOLDEN GATE BAKERY, &nbsp;LOCATED AT 1029 GRANT AVE - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;EGG CUSTARD TARTS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - THE BUENA VISTA, LOCATED AT 2765 HYDE ST - (FAMOUS FOR CRAB OMELETTE AND COFFEE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - BOUDIN BAKERY, LOCATED AT PIER 39 SPACE 5-Q - (FAMOUS FOR CHOWDER ( IS A TYPE OF SOUP OR STEW PREPARED WITH MILK OR CREAM) IN A BREAD BOWL)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - THE GRUBSTAKE, LOCATED AT 1525 PINE ST - {FAMOUS FOR CALDO VERDE IS A SOUP MADE FROM &nbsp;POTATOES, COLLARD GREENS (OR KALE)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - SWENSEN&#39;S, LOCATED AT 1999 HYDE ST. - (FAMOUS FOR CHOCOLATE ICE CREAM)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - TROUBLE COFFEE, &nbsp;LOCATED AT 4033 JUDAH ST. - (FAMOUS FOR TOASTED BRIOCHE ARE SLATHERED WITH BUTTER CRUSTED WITH CINNAMON AND SUGAR)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - &nbsp;ZANZE&#39;S, LOCATED AT 2405 OCEAN AVE. - (FAMOUS FOR CHEESECAKE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>9 - TARTINE, LOCATED AT 600 GUERRERO ST. - {FAMOUS FOR CROQUE-MONSIEUR IS A SANDWICH MADE FROM BREAD, EGGS, BUTTER, BOILED HAM, CHEESE (TYPICALLY EMMENTAL), PEPPER AND SALT}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>10 - Z &amp; Y RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT 655 JACKSON ST. - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN WITH &nbsp;CHILI PEPPER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>11 - ZUNI CAFE, LOCATED AT 1658 MARKET ST. - (FAMOUS FOR ROASTED CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>12 - CHINO&#39;S TAQUERIA, LOCATED AT 3416 BALBOA ST. - (FAMOUS FOR CHICHARRON IS A DISH MADE FROM PORK)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>13 - MR. HOLMES BAKEHOUSE, LOCATED AT 1042 LARKIN ST. - (FAMOUS FOR CROISSANT IS A TYPE OF PASTRY MADE FROM YEAST, DOUGH, BUTTER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>14 - MARLOWE, LOCATED AT 500 BRANNAN ST. - (FAMOUS FOR BURGERS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>15 - 20TH CENTURY CAFE, LOCATED AT 198 GOUGH ST. - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;HONEY CAKE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>16 - OUTERLANDS, LOCATED AT 4001 JUDAH ST. - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;PANCAKE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>17 - YASUKOCHI&#39;S SWEET STOP, LOCATED AT 1790 SUTTER ST. - (FAMOUS FOR COFFEE CRUNCH CAKE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>18 - SAN TUNG, LOCATED AT 1031 IRVING ST. - (FAMOUS FOR NOODLES WITH PEANUT SAUCE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>19 - PERILLA, LOCATED AT 836 IRVING ST. - (FAMOUS FOR GARLIC NOODLES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>20 - ARIZMENDI, LOCATED AT 1331 9TH AVE. - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;PIZZA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>21 - LIBA, LOCATED AT &nbsp;380 17TH ST. - (FAMOUS FOR FALAFEL SALAD WITH SWEET POTATO FRIES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>22 - SAN FRANCISCO - {FAMOUS FOR CROQUE-MONSIEUR IS A SANDWICH MADE FROM BREAD, EGGS, BUTTER, BOILED HAM, CHEESE, PEPPER ; CIOPPINO IS A TYPE OF FISH STEW MADE FROM SEAFOOD ( CRAB, CLAMS, SHRIMP, SCALLOPS, SQUID, MUSSELS), FISH, TOMATOES, WINE ; FORTUNE COOKIE IS A CRISPY COOKIE USUALLY MADE FROM FLOUR, SUGAR, VANILLA, AND SESAME SEED OIL}</strong></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(771, 16, 43, 1564, 'Washington', 'U.S.A', 'SEATTLE', 'buildings-1846133_640.jpg', 'buildings-1846133_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Seattle is the largest city in both the state of Washington and the Pacific North west region of North America. A major gateway for trade with Asia Seattle is the 3rd largest port in North America in terms of container handling. Seattle&#39;s climate is oceanic or temperate marine with cool wet winters and warm dry summers. Seattle has a left coast vibe with a high tech spin. Well known for its rain Seattle is a city sandwiched between the salt water of Puget Sound and the fresh water of Lake Washington and to the north is the Canadian province of British Columbia. Nicknamed the Emerald City because of its abundant evergreen trees, Seattle is the cultural and business centre of the Pacific Northwest as well as a popular holiday destination. Seattle is known for museums, sightseeing, parks, nightlife and zoos &amp; aquariums. Famous for its addiction to caffeine and as the birthplace to bands such as Nirvana and Pearl Jam, there is a lot to mark Seattle out as an important place on the map. Seattle has a very relaxed and friendly vibe. There&rsquo;s a robust music scene here great bars and world class sea food.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are three main areas to stay in Seattle. Downtown is a pretty compact area to explore by foot or bus. There are three main hotel districts within the city. The main area of downtown is the Pine corridor bordered approximately by 1st to 8th Ave. and from Pine to James Street. A newer area with many hotels is the South Lake Union neighbourhood. The third main area for hotels and motels would be the area concentrated around the Space Needle and Seattle Centre. This can be a good area for families or those looking for more budget friendly options.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The city&#39;s primary commercial airport is Seattle Tacoma International Airport locally known as Sea-Tac Airport is served by a number of airlines connecting the region with international, national and domestic destinations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Sound Transit&rsquo;s Link light rail makes trips from Angle Lake Station to the University of Washington through downtown Seattle making 14 stops along the way, including downtown Seattle and Sea-Tac Airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- The closest thing to a central bus station is the Greyhound Terminal which is served by various bus companies that serve to and from the city of Seattle.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Interstate Highway 5 cuts through the middle of Seattle north to south. I-90 run from I-5 interchange in Seattle all the way to Boston and crosses one of the two Lake Washington bridges to Bellevue, along with SR-520 further north. I-405 runs parallel to I-5 on the east side of Lake Washington.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water </strong>- There are regular ferry services in the Seattle area. Cruise ships to Seattle may be docked at one of two terminals in the Port of Seattle.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around </strong>- One can walk around most neighbourhoods of interest in Seattle and there&#39;s a light rail system that connects a few of the neighbourhoods. Buses in the city do connect many areas. Travelling by car and biking in Seattle can be a fun and efficient way to explore the city. An all day regional transit pass is available for visitors to Seattle.</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - MEE SUM PASTRY, LOCATED AT 1526 PIKE PL - (FAMOUS FOR BEEF CURRY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - HEAVEN SENT,&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT 14330 LAKE CITY WAY NE. - (FAMOUS FOR FRIED CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - DELANCEY, LOCATED AT 1415 NW., 70TH ST. - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;CHOCOLATE COOKIE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - WEDGWOOD BROILER, LOCATED AT 8230 35TH AVE., NE. - (&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;FAMOUS FOR CHEESEBURGER WITH SALAD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - MAWADDA CAFE, LOCATED AT 4433 S., GRAHAM ST. - (FAMOUS FOR FALAFEL IS A DEEP FRIED BALL MADE FROM FAVA BEANS OR CHICKPEAS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - MOLLY MOON&rsquo;S, LOCATED AT 917 E PINE ST. - (FAMOUS FOR ICE-CREAM)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - PIROSHKY PIROSHKY, LOCATED AT 1908 PIKE PL - {FAMOUS FOR PIROSHKIES IS FRIEF DOUGH FOOD WHICH CONSISTS CONTAIN MEAT (TYPICALLY BEEF) OR A VEGETABLE FILLING (MASHED POTATOES, MUSHROOMS, ONIONS AND EGG, OR CABBAGE)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - PORKCHOP &amp; CO., LOCATED AT 5451 LEARY AVE., NW - (FAMOUS FOR SHAKSHOUKA IS A DISH MADE FROM EGGS POACHED IN A TOMATO SAUCE, CHILI PEPPERS, AND ONIONS, OFTEN SPICED WITH CUMIN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>9 - HITCHCOCK, LOCATED AT 133 WINSLOW WAY E. BAINBRIDGE ISLAND&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; - {FAMOUS FOR GNOCCHI IS A TYPE OF DUMPLING MADE FROM POTATOES (OR SEMOLINA OR WHEAT FLOUR OR BREADCRUMBS); SOMETIMES EGGS, CHEESE}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>10 - WESTWARD, LOCATED AT 2501 N., NORTHLAKE WAY - (FAMOUS FOR GRAVLAX IS A DISH MADE FROM RAW SALMON, CURED IN SALT, SUGAR, AND DILL)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>11 - MANOLIN, LOCATED AT 3621 STONE WAY N. - (FAMOUS FOR CHICHARR&oacute;N IS A DISH MADE FROM PORK, &nbsp;MUTTON, OR BEEF AND PIG SKIN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>12 - NIRMAL&#39;S, LOCATED AT 106 OCCIDENTAL AVE., S - (FAMOUS FOR VINDALOO IS A CURRY DISH MADE FROM VINEGAR, SUGAR, GINGER, SPICES, CHILI PEPPERS)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(772, 16, 43, 1540, 'Massachusetts', 'U.S.A', 'BOSTON', 'boston-1982421_640.jpg', 'boston-1982421_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">One of North America&#39;s most beautiful travel destinations Boston is a city of pleasing contradictions where new discoveries meet historic sites. Explore the legendary Freedom Trail where narrow streets recall a history of revolution and transformation. Soak in the breathtaking urban and waterfront scenery while enjoying lush parks, diverse neighbourhoods and an impressive legacy of art, culture and entertainment. With a remarkable blend of historical sites and modern attractions Boston is a unique cultural destination that invites wonder and excitement. Boston is a walk able city accommodating exciting neighbourhoods, Red Sox fans and some vintage streets with cobblestones pavements. Boston takes pride of its rich history and is counted as one of the oldest cities in America. Boston is the largest city in New England the capital of Massachusetts one of the most historic wealthy and influential cities in the US. Museums, historic sites, plenty of live performances these are just some of the reasons why every year the city welcomes more than 16 million guests. Boston is among the ten most popular tourist destinations of the country.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">To stay close to where most of Boston&#39;s tourist action is, book a room at one of the many hotels located downtown near the centre of the city and state governments, businesses, and shopping. For a more affordable option, consider a budget friendly boutique hotel or small bed and breakfast in one of the city&#39;s diverse residential neighbourhoods. Back Bay is the best area to stay in Boston away from the noisy crowds. It is a picturesque Victorian style neighbourhood close to the Charles River, and offers great connectivity to historic sites, and the subway.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- The Logan International Airport welcomes flights from selected International cities along with cities across the country which is the major way to get in Boston.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Amtrak rail services enable tourists to traverse to nearby cities from Boston.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- Buses from various companies are available for commuting to cities around Boston.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water </strong>- The Black Falcon Cruise Terminal is the port in Boston for cruise ships. Water shuttles and taxis can be taken to reach Cambridge which is just a river away from Boston.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - Boston is a walk friendly city. Unless need to go away from the city centre one can cover the distance on foot. For distant locations, the subway system is the best option. Along with subway system, the MBTA also provides bus and water shuttle services. Other ways to get around some parts of the city include using a taxi or water taxi.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - NEPTUNE OYSTER, LOCATED AT 63 SALEM ST., # 1 - (FAMOUS FOR LOBSTER ROLL)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - CUTTY&#39;S, LOCATED AT 284 WASHINGTON ST. - (FAMOUS FOR ROAST BEEF SANDWICH)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - THE COAST CAFE, LOCATED AT 233 RIVER ST. - (FAMOUS FOR FRIED CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - ALDEN &amp; HARLOW, LOCATED AT 40 BRATTLE ST. - (FAMOUS FOR BURGERS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - ALIVE &amp; KICKING, LOCATED AT 269 PUTNAM AVE. - (FAMOUS FOR LOBSTER SANDWICH)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - SOFRA BAKERY &amp; CAFE, LOCATED AT 1 BELMONT ST. - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;EGG SANDWICH)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n7 - DURGIN-PARK, LOCATED AT 340 N MARKET ST. - (FAMOUS FOR BAKED BEANS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - SAUS BOSTON, LOCATED AT 33 UNION ST. - (FAMOUS FOR POUTINE FRIES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>9 - MARIA&#39;S, LOCATED AT 46 CROSS ST. - {FAMOUS FOR CANNOLI IS FRIED DOUFH PASTRY FILLING WITH RICOTTA (CHEESE)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>10 - T ANTHONY&#39;S PIZZERIA, LOCATED AT 1016 COMMONWEALTH AVENUE - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN PARM SANDWICH)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>11 - FLOUR BAKERY &amp; CAFE, LOCATED AT 1595 WASHINGTON ST., (AT RUTLAND ST.,) - (FAMOUS FOR FRENCH TOAST WITH REAL MAPLE SYRUP)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>12 - MIKE&#39;S CITY DINER, LOCATED AT 1714 WASHINGTON ST. - (FAMOUS FOR PANCAKES, WAFFLES, AND OMELETTE)</strong></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(773, 16, 43, 1533, 'Illinois', 'U.S.A', 'CHICAGO', 'junction-1756853_640.jpg', 'junction-1756853_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Chicago is the classical American city that offers world class culture with zero attitudes. Chicago is the 3rd largest city in the United States. The windy city has a rich history and plenty of attractions that appeal to visitors of all ages. Chicago boasts a large number of tourist attractions but there are undoubtedly select handfuls that are by far the most popular with visitors. It&rsquo;s best to visit Chicago in the spring or in fall when temperatures are warm and the city offers plenty of festivals and activities. Peak travel season occurs during the summer months when the weather is at its warmest though the high season means larger crowds and higher prices at hotels. Winters in Chicago can be chilly and snowy but tourists may want to brave a blizzard or two for the lower airfare and hotel prices. There is amazing number of free things to do in Chicago. Tourists will be surprised at how many free attractions, galleries and museums there are as well as lots of free events. With several of the world&rsquo;s tallest buildings located here Chicago is a showcase for modern masterpieces and historic landmarks by America&rsquo;s greatest architects including Frank Lloyd Wright, Daniel Burnham and Louis Sullivan. The River walk can also serve as a launching point for an architecture tour or canoe trip down the Chicago River.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\nThe Midwest&#39;s major centre for business conventions Chicago boasts many affordable places to stay with most hotels located around the airport and the city&#39;s central business district. To discover the city from a comfortable base within walking distance of most tourist attractions, aim for one of the big chain hotels in the downtown area. If travelling on a limited budget and wish to get a deeper sense of Chicago&#39;s many diverse neighbourhoods consider staying away from the pricey city centre and explore suburbs on a commuter train line for easy city access.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - O&#39;Hare International Airport is the main airport in Chicago where most of the international airlines land. The other airport is Chicago Midway International Airport generally for low cost carriers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Amtrak provides services to travel to major cities in the United States with a stop at Chicago.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- Buses can be taken to reach cities around Chicago. A number of companies offer buses to different cities and the stop in Chicago varies from one company to another.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- The Stevenson Expressway will take tourists from the southwest city and the southwest suburbs to downtown Chicago. The Dan Ryan south of downtown comes in from Indiana to the east and from central Illinois. The Kennedy north of downtown comes in from the northwest city and northwest suburbs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around </strong>- The best way to get around is using &lsquo;L&rsquo; the subway system in Chicago. Other than that tourists can take a bus or taxi to cover distances. One can ride in a Metro Rail if planning to make way to Chicago Suburbs.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - ALBANO&#39;S PIZZERIA, LOCATED AT 5913 W ROOSEVELT RD. - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;BEEF SANDWICH)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - AU CHEVAL, LOCATED AT 800 W., RANDOLPH ST. - (FAMOUS FOR CHEESEBURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - CALUMET FISHERIES INC, LOCATED AT &nbsp;3259 E 95TH ST. - (FAMOUS FOR SMOKED SALMON)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - CRISP, LOCATED AT