(774, 16, 43, 1528, 'District of Columbia', 'U.S.A', 'WASHINGTON DC', 'the-white-house-1623005_640.jpg', 'the-white-house-1623005_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Capital of United States, Washington DC is a beneficiary of neoclassic beauty. A city which is not only famous for its museums and monuments but also for the cultural style it embosses with its nightlife, performing art venues and trendy shops. Washington DC is the lifeline of the US Federal government. History culture and art DC has it all as there are over a hundred museums and monuments to keep one engaged other than the most popular White House and the Capitol building. Washington has got a buoyant nightlife, mouth watering dining experiences, animated neighbourhoods and beautifully appreciated art galleries other than the landmark sites depicting vintage assets and narrating the tales of bygone times. Washington DC is always a delightful, educational and entertaining destination but there are good times and better times to make the journey to America&rsquo;s capital. It is best to go in spring or fall, when the weather is mild and the flowers are in bloom. A bustling hive of activity, Washington DC certainly exudes a powerful vibe. After all, it is the capital city of the most powerful country in the world. It is interesting to note that the city is not actually a part of any state in the United States. Rather, it was created purely as a seat of the government and is exclusively under the federal jurisdiction.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Most visitors to Washington DC end up in the East End the old downtown district containing most of the city&#39;s major cultural attractions. For a more authentic Washington experience, consider staying at smaller hotel just a little north or east of this busy area. Neighbourhoods outside downtown offer less expensive accommodations and affordable street parking as well as opportunities to meet more locals and fewer tourists. Alternatively, try a hotel in Georgetown packed with high end shops and Colonial architecture.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Washington Dulles International Airport in Sterlin, Virginia is the primary airport to reach DC. Another international airport is the Baltimore International Thurgood Marshall Airport, about 40 miles away in Baltimore, Maryland.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Amtrak provides great connectivity throughout the Northeast Corridor. Tourists can travel from Maryland in Maryland Rail Commuter or get a seat in Virginia Railway Express to reach DC from Virginia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Buses can be used to commute from nearby cities to the District. There are many bus companies which provide this service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - Metro rail is the most efficient way to get around Washington DC. Some other public transport options include metro buses and cabs. Driving in DC is a bad idea.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - FAST GOURMET, LOCATED AT 1400 W ST NW - (FAMOUS FOR CHIVITO IS A &nbsp;SANDWICH MADE FROM BUN, CHURRASCO BEEF, BACON, EGGS, HAM, BLACK OR GREEN OLIVES, MOZZARELLA, TOMATOES, MAYONNAISE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - HORACE &amp; DICKIE&#39;S, LOCATED AT 809 12TH ST NE. - (FAMOUS FOR FRIED FISH)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - CHINATOWN EXPRESS, LOCATED AT 746 6TH ST NW. - (FAMOUS FOR DUCK NOODLE SOUP)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - CANTINA MARINA, LOCATED AT 600 WATER ST SW. - (FAMOUS FOR NACHOS IS A SNACK MADE FROM TORTILLA CHIPS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - AREPA ZONE, LOCATED AT &nbsp;1309 5TH ST NE. - (FAMOUS FOR CACHAPA IS A TYPE OF PANCAKE MADE FROM CORN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - AMSTERDAM FALAFEL SHOP, LOCATED AT 2425 18TH ST NW. - (FAMOUS FOR FAFEL SANDWICH)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - ROSE&#39;S LUXURY, LOCATED AT 717 8TH ST., SE. - (FAMOUS FOR PORK SAUSAGE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - STONEY&#39;S ON L, LOCATED AT 2101 L ST NW. SUITE #103 - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN SANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>9 - THE MARKET LUNCH, LOCATED AT 225 7TH ST., SE - (FAMOUS FOR PANCAKES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>10 - RASIKA WEST END, LOCATED AT 1190 NEW HAMPSHIRE AVE., NW - (FAMOUS FOR TANDOORI LAMB CHOPS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>11 - BOSS SHEPHERD&#39;S, LOCATED AT 513 13TH ST., NW - (FAMOUS FOR FRIED CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>12 - GOOD STUFF EATERY, LOCATED AT 303 PENNSYLVANIA AVE., SE - (FAMOUS FOR MILKSHAKES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>13 - BREAD FURST, LOCATED AT 4434 CONNECTICUT AVE., NW - (FAMOUS FOR CHOCOLATE COOKIES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>14 - BOUNDARY STONE, LOCATED AT 116 RHODE ISLAND AVE., NW - (FAMOUS FOR SPICY ROASTED NUTS &nbsp;AND HONEY HOT WINGS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>15 - JUDY, LOCATED AT 2212 14TH ST., NW - {FAMOUS FOR PUPUSA IS A TYPE OF SANDWICH MADE FROM CORN TORTILLA(FLATBREAD) FILLINGS WITH MEAT, FISH, CHEESE, VEGETABLES}</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(775, 16, 43, 1525, 'California', 'U.S.A', 'LOS ANGELES', 'santa-monica-pier-1630451_640.jpg', 'santa-monica-pier-1630451_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Los Angeles is the hub of all activities on the famous West Coast of the United States. It is the second largest city in the entire country, and one of the US&#39;s prime tourist cities. It is a great centre of sports, performance arts, cultures, people and this vibrant atmosphere can be witnessed while travelling this wonderful metropolis. This metropolis located on the Pacific coast of the USA is one of the most important cities in the country. Home to the world famous Hollywood entertainment industry, Los Angeles has become a huge tourist destination. The Los Angeles County is a huge area, and within it are some of the best activities and attractions to visit during a holiday. The city has such a wide array of places of interests, the most diverse tourists and travellers will find things to do for the entire week. Shoppers can go crazy in any of the numerous shopping malls and centres in the city, and foodies will have a ball of a time at the variety of cuisines and especially the historic Farmers Market. Los Angeles is also home to museums displaying some of the most stunning collections of natural history, like skeletons of dinosaurs and Ice Age animals among several other things. The luxury and sports cars plying around the streets of Los Angeles and the Peterson Museum and the Nethercutt Collection make Los Angeles a city of supreme entertainment for the car enthusiast as well.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Los Angeles may be synonymous with luxury, but its accommodations include not only some of the most opulent and expensive hotels in the world, but also budget priced hostels and inexpensive inns. In Los Angeles, a car opens up a world of lodging options, allowing tourists to stay outside the city proper and still have easy access to most major tourist attractions. If don&#39;t mind splurging, consider Hollywood or Beverly Hills. To save money, stay near the airport or in the eastern suburbs of the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The Los Angeles International Airport (LAX) is a huge and bustling and one of the busiest in the US. It is very well connected to the entire country and indeed the rest of the world with flights from all the major countries and cities in the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Los Angeles is fairly well connected to nearby destinations with trains arriving at the Union Station. Many train services like Union Pacific, Amtrak and Northern Santa Fe connect Los Angeles to the rest of the cities in the United States.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Long distance buses, shuttle buses, and airport buses all serve efficiently in connecting Los Angeles to the cities nearby. There are several bus companies such as the famous Greyhound, Bolt Bus, Megabus and Santa Barbara Airbus etc. which run along these routes to cities like Las Vegas, San Francisco, San Diego, San Jose, Oakland and many other locations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water</strong> - The city has 2 primary ports, Port of Los Angeles and the Port of Long Beach. Several international cruise liners and yachts arrive at these ports, and Los Angeles is one of the prime destinations on the west coast of the US and also in the entire Pacific region.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Los Angeles is easily accessible from nearby cities and towns. The Los Angeles Metropolitan Area has a plethora of highways and freeways into the city. The most popular of these are Interstate 10, which runs from one coast of the US to the other, to Florida Interstate 5, which runs southwards through San Diego all the way to Mexico and northwards to Sacramento, Portland and Seattle all the way to Canada and the US Route 101 which connects it to San Francisco.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - The Metro Rail and the public bus are the two most popular means of mass public transport here at Los Angeles. Various different companies provide bus services in the city, and the subway system runs across 8 lines. Cabs also run throughout the city, though one will have to book them.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - LANGER&#39;S DELI &amp; RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT 704 S ALVARADO ST - (FAMOUS FOR PASTRAMI SANDWICH)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - SQIRL, LOCATED AT 720 N VIRGIL AVE #4 - (FAMOUS FOR CRISPY RICE SALAD WITH &nbsp;EGG AND SAUSAGE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - PETIT TROIS, LOCATED AT 718 HIGHLAND AVE - (FAMOUS FOR OMELETTE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - THE APPLE PAN, LOCATED AT 10801 W PICO BLVD - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - PITA KITCHEN, LOCATED AT 14500 VENTURA BLVD, SHERMAN OAKS - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN KAFTA WITH EGGPLANT SALAD, AND HUMMUS IS A DISH MADE FROM CHICKPEAS OR OTHER BEANS, BLEND WITH TAHINI, OLIVE OIL, LEMON JUICE AND GARLIC)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6- ORIGINAL TOMMY&#39;S HAMBURGERS, LOCATED AT 2575 BEVERLY BLVD, - (FAMOUS FOR CHILI CHEESEBURGER AND HOTDOGS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - REPUBLIQUE, LOCATED AT 624 SOUTH LA BREA AVE - (FAMOUS FOR KIMCHI IS A DISH MADE FROM VEGETABLES LIKE CABBAGE AND RADISH)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - HONEY&#39;S KETTLE, LOCATED AT 9537 CULVER BLVD, CULVER CITY - (FAMOUS FOR FRIED CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>9 - GOLDEN DELI RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT 815 W LAS TUNAS DR, SAN GABRIEL - (FAMOUS FOR EGG ROLLS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>10 - PINK&#39;S, &nbsp;LOCATED AT 709 N LA BREA AVE - (FAMOUS FOR HOTDOGS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>11 - THE OINKSTER, LOCATED AT 2005 COLORADO BLVD - (FAMOUS FOR PASTRAMI SANDWICH AND PIGGY FRIES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>12 - GUISADO&#39;S, LOCATED AT 2100 EAST CESAR E CHAVEZ AVENUE - (FAMOUS FOR TACO IS A DISH MADE FROM TORTILLAS, MEAT, VEGETABLES, CHEESE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>13 - PIZZANISTA, LOCATED AT 2019 E. 7TH STREET, LOS ANGELES - (FAMOUS FOR CHEESE PIZZA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>14 - DIDDY RIESE, LOCATED AT 926 BROXTON AVE - (FAMOUS FOR ICE CREAM SANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>15 - FAT SAL&#39;S, LOCATED AT 1300 HIGHLAND AVE - (FAMOUS FOR SANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>16 - PHILIPPE THE ORIGINAL, LOCATED AT 1001 N. ALAMEDA STREET - (FAMOUS FOR SANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>17 - OI ASIAN FUSION, LOCATED AT 7242 CANOGA AVENUE, CANOGA PARK - (FAMOUS FOR DYNAMITE FRIES IS A SNACK MADE FROM BEEF, RED BEANS, RED SAUCE, ONION, CUMIN, SALT AND PEPPER, CHILY , RED PEPPER.)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>18 - &nbsp;PORTO&#39;S BAKERY, LOCATED AT BURBANK, GLENDALE, AND DOWNEY - (FAMOUS FOR CHEESE PASTRIES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>19 - MASA OF ECHO PARK, LOCATED AT 1800 WEST SUNSET BLVD - (FAMOUS FOR CROISSANT BREAD PUDDING IS A DISH MADE FROM EGG YOLKS, SUGAR, VANILLA AND RAISINS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>20 - BLACK HOGG, LOCATED AT 2852 SUNSET BLVD - {FAMOUS FOR POPCORN BACON (DEEP FRIED CHUNKS OF BACON WITH MAPLE CREMA)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>21 - EL CHATO, LOCATED AT 5300 W OLYMPIC BLVD - (FAMOUS FOR TACOS IS A DISH COMPOSED OF A CORN OR WHEAT TORTILLA FILLING WITH MEAT, VEGETABLES, CHEESE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>22 - SARITA&rsquo;S PUPUSERIA, LOCATED AT 317 S. BROADWAY, GRAND CENTRAL MARKET - (FAMOUS FOR PUPUSA IS A TYPE OF SANDWICH MADE FROM CORN MASA FLOUR FILLING WITH MEAT, FISH, CHEESE, VEGETABLES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>23 - DOUGHBOYS, LOCATED AT 8136 W. THIRD STREET - (FAMOUS FOR RED VELVET CAKE IS A TPE OF CAKE MADE FROM FLOUR, BUTTER, SUGAR, BUTTERMILK, COCOA POWDER, OR CREAM CHEESE, BEETROOT OR RED FOOD COLORING)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>24 - DIDDY RIESE, LOCATED AT 926 BROXTON AVENUE, WESTWOOD - (FAMOUS FOR ICE CREAM AND COOKIE SANDWICH)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', '');
