(776, 16, 43, 1547, 'Nevada', 'U.S.A', 'LAS VEGAS', 'destination-1853477_640.jpg', 'destination-1853477_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Las Vegas a place that in today&#39;s date needs absolutely no introduction. Just hearing the name will make one picture the neon sign boards, the iconic hotels and the legendary casinos. Nicknamed the &lsquo;Entertainment Capital of the World&#39;, &#39;Sin City&#39; and &#39;City of Lights&#39;, Las Vegas is truly the place where dreams come true. The biggest city in the state of Nevada, Las Vegas is located in Clark County, within the Mojave Desert and is enclosed by barren hills on all sides. The city is known for its casinos, luxury hotels, fine dining restaurants, entertainment events and nightlife. It is one of the top tourist destinations in the world. The location for countless movie shoots, Las Vegas has a fantasy like environment with sparkling lights, towering buildings, themed hotels and dancing fountains. The Las Vegas Strip called the &#39;Strip&#39; is a 6.8 kms stretch on the Las Vegas Boulevard that is lined with casinos and resort hotels. Some of the hotels with the most number of rooms in the world are located on this strip. There are also outdoor adventures like zip lining, race car driving, horse riding and a host of desert activities. Often an adult getaway destination, the city has made an effort in recent years to expand its family friendly attractions. Part of the city&#39;s charm is its constantly changing landscape of high rises, often an unusual mix of elegance and kitsch.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">In Las Vegas, lodging options are plentiful. Visitors find a welcoming assortment of Las Vegas hotels with prices to fit just about any budget and amenities to suit most tastes. Business travellers can take advantage of national chains that cater to those with work to do. Families and vacationers can sleep comfortably and cheaply and business travellers find these hotels affordable, attractive options as well. Las Vegas is home to the most luxurious hotel and resorts in the world.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>By Air </strong>- Las Vegas is served by the McCarran International Airport, one of the busiest airports in the world with high volumes of passenger traffic. The airport is served by multiple airlines which provide service to destinations throughout North America, Europe and Asia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- Las Vegas is well connected to other cities in the state of Nevada and also to other states in America, via bus routes. Most Americans make spontaneous weekend trips to Las Vegas. Hence, there are regular buses from most cities. Greyhound buses are the preferred choice as they are comfortable and air conditioned.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- There are actually no direct rail services coming into Las Vegas. Amtrak Thruway Motor coach shuttles passengers between major cities and the nearest Amtrak stations. Amtrak&#39;s Southwest Chief operates a daily service from California, Albuquerque and Los Angeles to Kingman in Arizona, located 179 kms south of Las Vegas.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around </strong>- The Regional Transportation Commission of Southern Nevada operates around 49 routes within the valley. Taxis are a popular way to get around Las Vegas. Visitors staying in Vegas for two days or longer can rent cars. The Las Vegas Monorail operates along the east side of the Las Vegas Strip but it stops at the back entrance of the hotels and the Convention Centre. Most hotels are close to each other so walking is a great way to travel in Las Vegas.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - ESTIATORIO MILOS, LOCATED AT 3708 S LAS VEGAS BLVD - (FAMOUS FOR SEAFOOD DISHES)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - HOLSTEINS, LOCATED AT 3708 S LAS VEGAS BLVD. - (FAMOUS FOR BURGERS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - BATTISTA&#39;S HOLE IN THE WALL, LOCATED AT 4041 LINQ LN. - (FAMOUS FOR SPAGHETTPLE &nbsp;IS A TYPE OF PASTA MADE FROM SEMOLINA OR FLOUR AND WATER, AND CIOPPINO IS A FISH STEW MADE FROM SEAFOOD LIKE ( CRAB, CLAMS, SHRIMP, SCALLOPS, SQUID, MUSSELS), FISH, TOMATOES, WINE)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - CARNEVINO, LOCATED AT 3325 S LAS VEGAS BLVD. - (FAMOUS FOR STEAK SANDWICH AND LAMB CHOPS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n5 - PANCHOS, LOCATED AT 4865 S PECOS ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR ENCHILADA IS A CORN TORTILLA ROLLED &nbsp;FILLING WITH A CHILI PEPPER SAUCE, MEATS, CHEESE, BEANS, POTATOES AND VEGETABLES , POZOLE IS A TYPE OF SOUP MADE FROM HOMINY(DRIED MAIZE ), MEAT (PORK) AND CHILE PEPPERS)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - GO VEGAN CAFE, LOCATED AT 5875 S RAINBOW BLVD. - (FAMOUS FOR COFFEE, PANCAKES, WAFFLES)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n7 - VEGENATION, LOCATED AT 616 CARSON AVE. - (FAMOUS FOR VEGGIE BURGER)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n8 - VEGE-WAY, LOCATED AT 6410 N DURANGO DR. - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN SANDWICH, FISH TACOS, FRIES, AND MILKSHAKES)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n9 - VIOLETTE&#39;S VEGAN ORGANIC CAFE, LOCATED AT 8560 W DESERT INN ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR BURGERS AND COFFEE)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n10 - VEGGIEAT XPRESS, LOCATED AT 3768 MARYLAND PKWY STE 650, INSIDE THE 99 RANCH MARKET - (FAMOUS FOR TOMATO RICE NOODLE SOUP, BEEF SANDWICHES AND EGG ROLLS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n11 - BAGUETTE CAFE, LOCATED AT 8359 W SUNSET ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR FRENCH PASTRIES AND SANDWICHES)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n12 - BEERHAUS, LOCATED AT 3784 S LAS VEGAS BLVD. - (FAMOUS FOR HOG DOGS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n13 - FRUITS &amp; ROOTS COLD PRESSED JUICE BAR AND WELLNESS KITCHEN, LOCATED AT &nbsp;7885 W SUNSET ROAD 180 - (FAMOUS FOR JUICE)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&n