(777, 16, 43, 1525, 'California', 'U.S.A', 'SAN DIEGO', 'usa-1644670_640.jpg', 'usa-1644670_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Home to serene white sand beaches, San Diego is popularly called America&#39;s finest city. With incredible weather conditions throughout the year, tourists can never have a hard time enjoying your holiday in San Diego. San Diego is the second largest city in California, while it ranks no. 8 in the list of the largest cities in United States. In addition to mesmerizing beach views, San Diego also offers entertainment, informative tours and historical sightseeing. There are several museums, theme parks, historic parks and monuments which make this city a perfect destination for holidaying. San Diego is a great place to visit any time of the year. Its mild southern California climate ensures that, as do the many and varied activities designed to keep visitors from getting bored. This city by the bay offers something for everyone, from beach combers to shoppers and party animals. San Diego has it all.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">San Diego has a great set of accommodation options, ranging from hostels to luxury hotels. No matter which neighbourhood one chooses to stay in, he would be close to some or the other attraction of the city. Tourists can book a beach resort or look for a budget hostel in Downtown and opt for Bed and Breakfast in a houseboat or mansion or can choose a rental for personal choices. Offering accommodations at a wide range of price levels, San Diego is one of the easiest cities to stay in, regardless of whether simply passing through or hanging around for a long vacation.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - San Diego International Airport, also known as Lindbergh Field is the main landing point for visitors. More than a dozen airlines serve this airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - AMTRAK operates through San Diego connecting it to nearby cities. A commuter train is also operated by COASTER which provides limited and no services on weekends and Sunday respectively.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- Operators like Greyhound, Hoang Express, Inter Californias, Lux Bus and Mexi coach allow people to traverse to other cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water</strong> - The Cruise Ship Terminal in the city provides transportation to Los Angeles and Baja Mexico from the San Diego coast.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around </strong>- The most convenient way to get around the city is to rent a car. The streets laid on grid system are easy to navigate one just need to keep some coins handy for metered parking. Buses and trolleys can be taken to cover some major attractions in the city, but the MTS system is not very consistent. Plenty of taxis are available everywhere, but can cost pretty high.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - BUONA FORCHETTA, LOCATED AT 3001 BEECH ST - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - CAFE 21, LOCATED AT &nbsp;2736 ADAMS AVE - (FAMOUS FOR PANCAKE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - SEARSUCKER, LOCATED AT 611 FIFTH AVE - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN SANDWICH)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - TRULUCK&#39;S, LOCATED AT 8990 UNIVERSITY CENTER LN - (FAMOUS FOR CARROT CAKE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - HODAD&#39;S, LOCATED AT 5010 NEWPORT AVE - (FAMOUS FOR CHEESE BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - NICO&#39;S MEXICAN FOOD, LOCATED AT 4918 NEWPORT AVE - (&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;FAMOUS FOR BURRITO IS A FOOD MADE FROM FLOUR TORTILLAS, MEAT AND BEANS OR REFRIED BEANS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - PUESTO, LOCATED AT 789 W HARBOR DR - (FAMOUS FOR BU&nti