RDENS DR, ENCINITAS - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN PIE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>19 - IRONSIDE, LOCATED AT 1654 INDIA ST - (FAMOUS FOR LOBSTER ROLL AND CHOWDER FRIES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>19 - SICILIAN THING, LOCATED AT 4046 30TH ST - (FAMOUS FOR ALMOST LASAGNA &nbsp;MADE WITH RICOTTA AND MEATBALLS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>20 - KETTNER EXCHANGE, LOCATED AT 2001 KETTNER BLVD - (&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;FAMOUS FOR FRIED CHICKEN)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n21 - GREAT MAPLE, LOCATED AT 1451 WASHINGTON ST - (FAMOUS FOR PECAN PIE IS A DESERT MADE FROM PECAN AND CORN SYRUP FILLING WITH EGGS AND BUTTER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>22 - OB NOODLE HOUSE &amp; SAKE BAR, LOCATED AT 2218 CABLE ST - (FAMOUS FOR PHO IS A TYPE OF SOUP MADE FROM NOODLE AND BEEF OR CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>23 - DRAFT, LOCATED AT 3105 OCEAN FRONT WALK - (FAMOUS FOR LEMON MERINGUE PIE MILKSHAKE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>24 - ECLIPSE CHOCOLATE, LOCATED AT 2145 FERN ST - (FAMOUS FOR CRISPY QUINOA FRITTERS IS A FOOD MADE FROM QUINOA, EGGS, PARSLEY, MINT, ONION, GARLIC, FETA AND PLAIN FLOUR)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>25 - BASIC, LOCATED AT 410 TENTH AVE - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>26 - HASH HOUSE A GO GO, LOCATED AT 3628 FIFTH AVE - (FAMOUS FOR FRIED CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>27 - BABYCAKES, LOCATED AT 3766 FIFTH AVE - (FAMOUS FOR TRES LECHES CAKE ISA TYPE OF SPONGE CAKE MADE FROM CAKE BASE, MILK, AND CREAM)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n28 - CRAZEE BURGER, LOCATED AT 3993 30TH ST - (FAMOUS FOR BURGERS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>29 - CUCINA URBANA, LOCATED AT 505 LAUREL ST - (FAMOUS FOR PASTA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>30 - SAN DIEGO - (&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;FAMOUS FOR CARNE ASADA FRIES IS A FOOD MADE FROM FRENCH FRIES, CARNE ASADA, GUACAMOLE, SOUR CREAM, CHEESE)</strong></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(778, 16, 43, 1561, 'texas', 'U.S.A', 'DALLAS', 'bridge-936591_640.jpg', 'bridge-936591_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Dallas is located in North Texas. The Metroplex is the most populated area in Texas. The City of Dallas by itself is the third most populated in the state behind Houston and San Antonio. The city&#39;s prominence arose from its historical importance as a centre for the oil and cotton industries, and its position along numerous railroad lines, and also it is the largest urban centre of the fourth most populous metropolitan area in the United States. Located in the north central part of the state, Dallas is a prominent city in Texas and is one of the most populated metropolitan areas in the United States of America. The business reputation of Dallas rose from its historical status as the centre for cotton and oil industries. It was also positioned among numerous railroads. It is best to visit Dallas during the spring or autumn, because summer in this city can get uncomfortably hot. The mild spring temperatures give rise to vibrant and blooming wildflowers.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\nThere is a wide selection of chain hotels on the perimeter of the sprawling DFW Airport. These places are in various states of renovation and often turn up in Priceline searches. Priceline includes a huge list of zones in the Metroplex, and some of the rooms tourists might land will be too far from the desired location. One can pinpoint selections, a basic DFW hotel search. Rooms in four star hotels are also available here.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The Dallas/Fort Worth area is served by two major airports, Dallas Fort Worth International Airport, and Love Field. Love Field is home to Southwest Airlines and is much closer to downtown.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- There are two major Amtrak routes which go to Dallas Fort worth, the Texas Eagle between San Antonio and Chicago, and the Heartland Flyer between Fort Worth and Oklahoma City.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- There are many bus services ranging from ordinary bus to first class. Volane runs first class buses from Dallas to both Houston and Austin equipped with various amenities such as leather seats, electrical outlets, ample leg room and free Wi-Fi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- The simplest and most reliable way to get around Dallas is by car. Gas stations are plentiful and most sell both regular unleaded and diesel fuel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around </strong>- There are two main public transportation options in the city, DART and Super Shuttle service. The local light rail system is known as DART, and it provides 45 miles of service. Taxi rides into either downtown or consider using the Super Shuttle service, which is usually less expensive than a cab.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - THE GRAPE, LOCATED AT 2808 GREENVILLE AVE - (FAMOUS FOR MUSHROOM SOUP)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - BABE&#39;S CHICKEN DINNER HOUSE, LOCATED AT 104 N OAK ST - (FAMOUS FOR FRIED CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - HIGHLAND PARK SODA FOUNTAIN, LOCATED AT 3229 KNOX ST - (FAMOUS FOR GRILLED CHEESE &amp; TOMATO SOUP)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - KELLER&#39;S, LOCATED AT 6537 NORTHWEST HWY - (FAMOUS FOR HAMBURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - NORMA&#39;S CAFE, LOCATED AT 17721 DALLAS PKWY - (FAMOUS FOR PIE &nbsp;IS A BAKED DISH MADE FROM PASTRY DOUGH &nbsp;FILLING WITH VARIOUS SWEET OR SAVOURY INGREDIENTS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - OFF-SITE KITCHEN, LOCATED AT 331 SINGLETON BLVD - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;GREEN CHILE AND BACON BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - MONKEY KING, LOCATED AT 2933 MAIN ST, DALLAS - (FAMOUS FOR BEEF NOODLE SOUP)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - MAPLE &amp; MOTOR, LOCATED AT 4810 MAPLE AVE - (FAMOUS FOR FRIED BALONEY SANDWICH)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>9 - RODEO GOAT, LOCATED AT 1926 MARKET CENTER BLVD - (FAMOUS FOR SHAKE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>10 - VINDU, LOCATED AT 4701 FRANKFORD RD #237 - (FAMOUS FOR NAAN, AND PANEER BUTTER MARSALA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>11 - COSMIC CAFE, LOCATED AT &nbsp;2912 OAK LAWN AVE - (FAMOUS FOR SAMOSA AND DAL FRY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>12 - CANE ROSSO, LOCATED AT &nbsp;7328 GASTON AVE - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA)</strong></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(779, 16, 43, 1561, 'texas', 'U.S.A', 'HOUSTON', 'houston-1402093_640.jpg', 'houston-1402093_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Houston named after former General Sam Houston who in 1836 won the Battle of San Jacinto which gained Texas its independence from Mexico is the fourth most populated city in North America and home to approximately two and a half million residents. It is a magnet for tourism, being closely linked with the Space Centre Houston and NASA&rsquo;s astronaut training and flight control complex together with many other interesting attractions. Houston serves up nationally recognized dining, shopping, entertainment and nightlife. &nbsp;It has world class attractions and events. &nbsp;Best of all, tourists will find a number of things that are budget friendly or free. Houston might not seem like much of a tourist town to locals people come here to work or go to school, not sightsee but it does attract thousands of tourists every year. With the conventions going on at the George R. Brown Convention Centre, the rodeo at Reliant Park, the various districts and year round schedule of professional sports Houston is on the vacation map for people from around the world.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">As the largest city in Texas, Houston contains a number of styles of hotels. Many high end luxury hotels are located in the Downtown and Uptown areas, as are a number of hotels geared towards business travellers. Houston bills itself as the Energy Capital of the World, so it&#39;s no surprise that it houses many green hotels, their garages designed to cater to electric vehicle owners. For something completely different enjoy a Texas country experience at a working ranch outside the city limits.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Houston is served by two major commercial airports and two smaller regional airports. The large airports are George Bush Intercontinental Airport and William P. Hobby Airport. The smaller airports are Sugar Land Regional Airport and Ellington Field.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Amtrak&#39;s Sunset Limited line is the only passenger train route with a stop in Houston although a daily bus provides a direct connection from the Houston Amtrak station to the Texas Eagle at Longview.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Megabus runs buses from Houston to Dallas, Austin, San Antonio, and New Orleans that departs from three different locations in Houston. Vonlane runs first class buses from Houston to both Austin and Dallas equipped with various amenities such as leather seats, ample leg room, free Wi-Fi, and satellite TV.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around </strong>- Houston has a number of freeways and toll ways that make getting around the metro area by car fairly easy. The Metro operates local and express bus lines, as well as a very popular light rail system called Metro Rail. Outside of Downtown, don&#39;t expect to catch a taxi on the streets, but there are various cab stands located at various parts of downtown proper. Houston is so spread out and humid and hot that bicycles are often best used for exercise or to get to somewhere that is close by.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - THE BREAKFAST KLUB, LOCATED AT 3711 TRAVIS ST - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;WINGS AND WAFFLES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - TONY&#39;S, LOCATED AT 3755 RICHMOND AVE - (FAMOUS FOR PANSOTI IS A PASTA TOPPED WITH AN AIRY PARMESAN PUFF)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - LANKFORD&#39;S GROCERY &amp; MARKET, LOCATED AT 88 DENNIS ST - (FAMOUS FOR CHEESEBURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - LES GIVRAL&#39;S, LOCATED AT 2704 MILAM ST - (FAMOUS FOR SANDWICHES AND SPRING ROLLS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><