(780, 16, 43, 1529, 'Florida', 'U.S.A', 'MIAMI', 'miami-936590_1920.jpg', 'miami-936590_19201.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Sultry, seductive Miami entertains many identities snowbird refuge, retiree haven, celebrity playground, immigrant stop off and tourist Mecca. All undeniably accurate, they&#39;re telling descriptors of everything this dazzling city embraces. They&#39;re also indicative of the melting pot culture that has come to define South Florida, an area originally dismissed by developers. The region later found purpose as a resort destination and as farm land for Florida&#39;s first settlers. These initial roles ultimately led to today&#39;s Miami a capital of travel commerce and self confident attraction. Miami is a seaport city famous for its beaches and nightlife. It is situated on the Atlantic Ocean side in South Florida. Many big companies and corporate houses have its headquarters in Miami as it is the financial, entertainment, arts and media hub of the country. Miami is referred to as Cruise capital of the World with cruise ships from all over the world docking at Port Miami. Other tourist destinations offer something for everyone while Miami offers multiple options for everyone from the trendy nightlife of the South Beach to the bustle of Calle Ocho and the highly energetic Little Havana. From the boat shows and auto racing to the amazing Art festivals and wine extravaganzas. The city of Miami offers all of these options, few among the never ending list.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">From containing hotels and other accommodation facilities starting from super luxury to the ones that won&rsquo;t make a dent in pocket, Miami has everything that will satisfy tourists. The hotels are all around the city, so finding a hotel won&rsquo;t be a hassle. Miami&#39;s South Beach boasts one of the largest collections of boutique hotels in the country. Though it can be quite expensive, staying in this area ensures proximity to the city&#39;s best shoreline, clubs, shopping, and restaurants.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Miami International airport and Fort Lauderdale International Airport are the two airports serving Miami.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Amtrak connects Miami to New York, Washington D.C. and other stations along the eastern coasts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Bus services like Red coach, Mega bus, ATC busses ply from nearby towns to Miami, mostly terminating at Miami International Airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water</strong> - Numerous cruise ships come to the Miami port from all over the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - Miami&#39;s public transit is among the best in the world. It is even possible to travel and explore complete Miami without taking taxi. Bus system covers the entire country and in recent times, they have become even more reliable. Two metro rail lines green and orange operate in the entire city. Taxis are expensive in the area. Another cheap option is to rent a car.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - EL PALACIO DE LOS JUGOS, LOCATED AT 7085 CORAL WAY - (FAMOUS FOR CHICHARRON IS A DISH MADE FROM PORK, CHICKEN, MUTTON, OR BEEF)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - LATINA MIAMI, LOCATED AT 3509 NE 2ND AVE - (FAMOUS FOR AREPA IS A TYPE OF FOOD MADE FROM CORN FLOUR AND STUFFED WITH CHEESE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - MY CEVICHE, LOCATED AT 1250 S MIAMI AVE - (FAMOUS FOR CEVICHE IS A SEAFOOD DISH MADE FROM &nbsp;FISH, LIME, LEMON, ONION AND CHILI PEPPER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - SERGIO&#39;S, LOCATED AT 3252 CORAL WAY CORAL GABLES - (FAMOUS FOR CROQUETTE IS A SMALL BREADCRUMBED FRIED FOOD ROLL MADE FROM MASHED POTATOES, GROUND MEAT, SHELLFISH, FISH, CHEESE, VEGETABLES AND MIX WITH BECHAMEL OR BROWN SAUCE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - VERSAILLES RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT 3555 SW 8TH ST - (FAMOUS FOR SANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - MICHAEL&#39;S GENUINE FOOD &amp; DRINK, LOCATED AT 130 NE 40TH ST - (FAMOUS FOR EGG DISHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - CHARLOTTE BAKERY, LOCATED AT 1499 WASHINGTON AVE, MIAMI BEACH - (FAMOUS FOR EMPANADA IS A STUFFED BREAD OR PASTRY, IT CONSIST OF MEAT, CHEESE, HUITLACOCHE, OR OTHER INGREDIENTS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - YARDBIRD SOUTHERN TABLE &amp; BAR, LOCATED AT 1600 LENOX AVE, MIAMI BEACH - (FAMOUS FOR FRIED CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>9 - PUERTO SAGUA, LOCATED AT 700 COLLINS AVE, MIAMI BEACH - {FAMOUS FOR FRIED PORK CHUNKS (MASITAS DE PUERCO FRITAS)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>10 - EL MAGO DE LAS, LOCATED AT 5828 SW 8TH ST - {FAMOUS FOR FRITA IS A DISH MADE FROM GROUND BEEF AND PORK PATTY (SOMETIMES MIXED WITH CHORIZO) ON BREAD AND TOPPED WITH &nbsp;POTATOES}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>11 - EATING HOUSE, LOCATED AT 804 PONCE DE LEON BLVD, CORAL GABLES - {FAMOUS FOR COCONUT MILK, ROASTED PEANUTS AND PANCAKES}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>12 - ICEBOX CAFE, LOCATED AT 1855 PURDY AVE, MIAMI BEACH - (FAMOUS FOR KEY LIME PIE IS A DESERT MADE FROM SHORTCRUST PIE SHELL, LIME JUICE, EGG YOLKS, SWEETENED CONDENSED MILK)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>13 - JIMMY&#39;Z KITCHEN WYNWOOD, LOCATED AT 2700 N MIAMI AVE - (FAMOUS FOR MOFONGO IS A DISH MADE FROM PLANTAINS, CHICHARRON, OLIVE OIL, AND GARLIC)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>14 - KARLA BAKERY, LOCATED AT 6476 W FLAGLER ST - (FAMOUS FOR PASTELITOS &nbsp;OR PASTELES IS A PUFF PASTRY FILLED WITH &nbsp;FRUITS