(781, 16, 41, 387, 'Ontario', 'CANADA', 'TORONTO', 'buildings-2297210_1920.jpg', 'buildings-2297210_19201.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The largest city in Canada and arguably the best known, Toronto is not the country&#39;s capital, but it is the Ontarian. Like a more civilised clean cut New York, Toronto has its skyscrapers downtown glitzy shopping in Yorkville and Bohemian districts in Queen Street West. It is also home to the CN Tower once the world&#39;s tallest at 1815 ft. Perched on the shores of the mighty Lake Ontario, Toronto is one of the most popular destinations in Canada. Drawing an eclectic mix of 21 million visitors every year, the formerly British Town of York has come a long way from its humble colonial beginnings. Toronto is the most populous city of Canada and the fifth largest city in North America is the financial capital of the county and one of the most multi culturally diverse cities of the word. Located on shore of the beautiful Lake Ontario, the city is known for its skyscrapers, museums, theatre, music and festivals. With no dearth of places to visit, to enjoy a meal at, take a stroll, or simply sit back and admire the things around one, Toronto can easily be the very epitome of a dream city to live in. A curious mix of all things fun and intriguing, there is something for anyone and everyone here. The numbers of cuisines offered are mindboggling and have achieved a level where their very taste leaves an everlasting cherish able memory on tongue. All in all, Toronto shall occupy a special place in the heart of the tourists.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">From low budget to luxury, Toronto is swarming with competitive hotels looking to help tourists resting head at night. Booking downtown is well worth it if want to be within walking distance of museums, sports venues and Toronto&rsquo;s subway system. There are many hotels that give good deals and provide exemplary services amalgamated with picturesque living spaces.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The city of Toronto is served by two airports Toronto Person International airport is country&#39;s principal airport and is well connected to the entire continent. It also serves as the base hub of Air Canada.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Rail networks such as Via Rail and AMTRAK connect to the city&#39;s Union Station bringing passengers from different parts of Canada.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - The city is well connected to other prominent cities by highways as well as US-Canada border crossing some of the bus services include Greyhound and Busbud.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Highways such as 2, 401 and 407, the Queen Elizabeth Link way connect the city to other cities which are within a range of 300 to 700 kilometres.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - Toronto is well connected by public transits provided by Toronto Transit Commission with a wide network of buses and subway. There is an internal train and bus network provided by GO Transit for Ontario region. Tourists can always choose from taxis that have a pre determined, non negotiable metered fare. Toronto also offers ferry trips about 15-20 minutes for certain destination on the coastlines.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - CAROUSEL BAKERY, LOCATED AT 93 FRONT ST, E - (FAMOUS FOR PEAMEAL BACON (BONELESS PORK LOIN) SANDWICH)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - KHAO SAN ROAD, LOCATED AT 11 CHARLOTTE ST - (FAMOUS FOR KHAO SOI IS A DISH MADE FROM &nbsp;RICE OR EGG NOODLES, COCONUT MILK, CURRY SOUP BASE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - LEE, LOCATED AT 601 KING ST, W - (FAMOUS FOR SLAW IS A TYPE OF SALAD MADE FROM RAW CABBAGE, VINAIGRETTE (VINEGAR ESSENCE), VEGETABLE OIL, SALT, MAYONNAISE AND SALAD CREAM)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - JUMBO, LOCATED AT 245 AUGUSTA AVE - (FAMOUS FOR EMPANADA IS A STUFFED BREAD OR PASTRY BAKED OR FRIED FILLING WITH MEAT, CHEESE, HUITLACOCHE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - CAPLANSKY&#39;S DELICATESSEN, LOCATED AT 356 COLLEGE ST - (FAMOUS FOR MEAT SANDWICH)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - TACOS EL ASADOR, LOCATED AT 689 BLOOR ST, W - (FAMOUS FOR PUPUSA IS A TYPE OF SANDWICH MADE FROM CORN &nbsp;FLOUR FILLINGS WITH MEAT, FISH, CHEESE AND VEGETABLES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - BANG BANG ICE CREAM &amp; BAKERY, LOCATED AT &nbsp;93A OSSINGTON AVE - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;ICE CREAM SANDWICH)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - SEVEN LIVES, LOCATED AT 69 KENSINGTON AVE - (FAMOUS FOR FISH TACOS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>9 - MOO FRITES, LOCATED AT 178 BALDWIN ST - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;BEEF FAT FRIED FRIES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>10 - POUTINI&rsquo;S HOUSE OF POUTINE, LOCATED AT 1112 QUEEN ST W - (FAMOUS FOR POUTINE IS A DISH MADE FROM FRENCH FRIES, GRAVY, CHEESE CURDS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>11 - THE DIRTY BIRD, LOCATED AT 79 KENSINGTON AVE - (FAMOUS FOR FRIED CHICKEN AND WAFFLES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>12 - GLORY HOLE DOUGHNUTS, LOCATED AT 1596 QUEEN ST, W - (FAMOUS FOR DONUT IS A TYPE OF &nbsp;FRIED DOUGH CONFECTIONERY OR DESSERT)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>13 - THE TEMPERED ROOM, LOCATED AT 1374 QUEEN ST W - (FAMOUS FOR CROISSANT IS A IS A BUTTERY, FLAKY, VIENNOISERIE PASTRY MADE FROM YEAST-LEAVENED DOUGH, BUTTER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>14 - PORCHETTA &amp; CO, LOCATED AT 825 DUNDAS ST, W - (FAMOUS FOR PORCHETTA IS A BONELESS PORK ROAST)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>15 - PHO TIEN THANH, LOCATED AT 57 OSSINGTON AVE - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;BEEF NOODLE SOUP)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n16 - HONEST WEIGHT, LOCATED AT 2766 DUNDAS ST W A - (FAMOUS FOR FISH SANDWICH)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>17 - BLACK CAMEL, LOCATED AT 4 CRESCENT ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR BEEF BRISKET SANDWICH)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>18 - UNCLE BETTY&#39;S, LOCATED AT 2590 YONGE ST - (FAMOUS FOR SANDWICH)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>19 - BROCK SANDWICH, LOCATED AT 1260 BLOOR ST W - (FAMOUS FOR CRISPY FENNEL SANDWICH)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>20 - BYMARK, LOCATED AT 66 WELLINGTON ST, W - (FAMOUS FOR BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>21 - GANDHI INDIAN CUISINE, LOCATED AT MUTTER PANEER ROTI - {FAMOUS FOR MUTTER PANEER ROTI(CHAPPATI)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>22 - BUSTER&rsquo;S SEA COVE, LOCATED AT 93 FRONT ST E - (FAMOUS FOR FISH AND CHIPS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>23 - MUSTAFA TURKISH PIZZA, LOCATED AT 866 WILSON AVE, NORTH YORK - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(782, 16, 41, 387, 'Ontario', 'CANADA', 'NIAGARA FALLS', 'niagara-falls-2112307_640.jpg', 'niagara-falls-2112307_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">One of the world&#39;s most stunning natural wonders Niagara Falls also offers visitors a host of small treasures that inspire on a completely different level. Blend the flash of the falls with the nostalgia and wineries of Niagara on the Lake and Twenty Valley or enjoy the beaches of St. Catharines and South Coast. Niagara Falls is all about exploring every nook and cranny of this city. From standing steps away from the falls to soaring through the sky on the Niagara Skywheel, almost all of the falls attractions are located in and around the Clifton Hill and Fallsview area. Straddling the Canadian and American sides of the Niagara River, Niagara Falls has a fantastic range of entertaining attractions to suit all kinds of visitors. Spectacular aerial views of the fall and the surrounding topography can be enjoyed from excellent observation points. The Skylon Tower has a mind blowing 360 degree panorama from its 160 mts high observation deck while the enormous Sky Wheel takes visitors on a magical journey into the clouds. Passports, visas and change at the ready make to way to the middle of the Rainbow Bridge which straddles the border between the two cities of Niagara Falls. Enjoy this unique perspective while posing for a photo with one foot in each country.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The Niagara region is home to quaint bed and breakfasts and high rise hotels that will wow anyone with the view. Hotels in Niagara Falls&#39; tourist area are brilliantly surrounded by a plethora of restaurants, shops and all the sights. If looking for something a little quieter, take to Niagara on the lake, it&#39;s a pristine town that is filled with a laid back aura. Rent a car while staying here to get the best of all the worlds this region includes.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Niagara Falls International Airport is the closest airport to the falls it is served by Spirit Airlines and Allegiant Air. On the Canadian side, Hamilton International Airport in Hamilton is about 70 kms from Niagara Falls and is served by West Jet.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The train service is provided as part of Amtrak&#39;s Toronto-New York Maple Leaf Train. The physical train is Amtrak&#39;s but is staffed by via during the Canadian Portion of the route.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Greyhound offer regular bus service to Niagara Falls from other Ontario cities. Megabus offers discount bus service to Niagara Falls from Toronto. The stop is near the Via Railway station. The Niagara Falls bus depot is located at Erie Avenue.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - Many of the main attractions are within walking distance near the falls and the rest are easily accessible by transit. The WEGO bus system runs on the Niagara Parkway along the river from May to October. There are stops at all the main points of interest along the parkway. Niagara Falls Taxi offers Taxi in Niagara Falls region.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - FLYING SAUCER RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT 6768 LUNDY&#39;S LN - (FAMOUS FOR MILKSHAKES, FISH AND CHIPS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - KOUTOUKI, LOCATED AT 5745 FERRY ST - (FAMOUS FOR PASTITSIO IS A PASTA DISH MADE FROM GROUND BEEF, BECHAMEL SAUCE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - SCOOPS &amp; MORE RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT 8123 LUNDY&#39;S LN - (FAMOUS FOR BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - BEAVERTAILS, LOCATED AT 4967 CLIFTON HILL - (FAMOUS FOR CAKES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - THE BIG SIZZLE BURGER, LOCATED AT 6683 FALLSVIEW BLVD - (FAMOUS FOR HAMBURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - PORTAGE BAKERY LTD, LOCATED AT 5845 GLADSTONE AVE - (FAMOUS FOR PASTRIES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - CONTINENTAL PANCAKE HOUSE &amp; FAMILY RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT 5810 STANLEY AVE - (FAMOUS FOR OMELETTE WITH CHEESE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - TRIPLE D&#39;S DINER, LOCATED AT 2895 ST PAUL AVE - (FAMOUS FOR SALMON SANDWICH)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>9 - NIKO&#39;S PLACE, LOCATED AT 5054 VICTORIA AVE - (FAMOUS FOR FISH AND CHIPS, &nbsp;HOT DOG AND POUTINE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>10 - THE JUKEBOX DINER, LOCATED AT 6332 THOROLD STONE ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR VARITIES OF SHAKES)&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', '');
