(783, 16, 41, 388, 'Qubec', 'Canada', 'MONTREAL', 'montreal-690737_640.jpg', 'montreal-690737_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Montreal is the second largest city in Canada. A city rich in culture and history, Montreal never fails to impress its visitors. Beautiful architecture, festive spirit, interesting museums and delicious cuisine it&rsquo;s sure to fall in love with this city full of life. Montreal has shades possibly more than a rainbow and that&#39;s the best thing about this metropolis. From old styled classic architectures to modern skylines, from fusion restaurants to authentic local food spots, from bustling markets to amazing museums, from religious buildings to an exuberant nightlife Montreal seems like a wish granting factory. The Notre Dame Basilica built in 1820s is probably the most charming architecture in the city. The Old Montreal and Mount Royal which is responsible for the name of the city are some places which will make the heart plead for permanently settling in these neighbourhoods. Montreal never disappoints, one just needs to breath in its essence in each of its mesmerizing elements. Downtown Montreal is home to McGill University and shopping venues, while Old Montreal contains a plethora of historic buildings, the oldest of which date back to the 17th century. Outdoor opportunities abound in Montreal including a network of cycling and walking paths through one of the city&#39;s many parks.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Primarily the best neighbourhoods in Montreal for tourists to get a hotel in are Downtown, Old Montreal and the Plateau. Old Montreal is full of charming old styled backdrops Downtown brings a cultural splash while Plateau is full of energy. Montreal&#39;s best lodging choices are found in historic Old Montreal. Old Montreal lodgings fit all budgets from simple hostels to old school European style luxury hotels.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - All major U.S. and Canadian airlines serve the Montreal-Trudeau airport along with some prominent international airlines.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Passenger trains are operated by Via Rail Canada connecting other parts of the country to Montreal. Amtrak also offers its service from Montreal to New York with various stops in between.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- A number of intercity bus operators provide services to reach Montreal such as Greyhound, Megabus, Orleans Express and Coach Canada.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - Tourists can easily navigate the city on foot or by using public transportation. There are metro and bus lines, which cover most parts of the city with several routes. Tourists can also hire a taxi or use Uber or Ola to get a cab.</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - MARCONI PIZZERIA, LOCATED AT 2222 RUE BEAUBIEN E - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - MA-AM-M BOLDUC, LOCATED AT 4351 LORIMIER AVE - (FAMOUS FOR POUTINE IS A DISH MADE FROM FRENCH FRIES, GRAVY, CHEESE CURDS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - MACHE, LOCATED AT 1655 ST DENIS ST - (FAMOUS FOR PATE CHINOIS IS A DISH MADE FROM GROUND BEEF, ONIONS, MAIZE OR CREAMED CORN, MASHED POTATOES VINEGAR)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - SCHWARTZ&#39;S, LOCATED AT 3895 ST LAURENT BLVD - (FAMOUS FOR SMOKED MEAT SANDWICH)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - AU PIED DE COCHON, LOCATED AT 536 AVENUE DULUTH E - (FAMOUS FOR POUDING CHOMEUR IS A A DESSERT MADE WITH WHITE CAKE BATTER AND A BROWN SUGAR AND CREAM SAUCE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - CHEZ MA TANTE, LOCATED AT 3180 RUE FLEURY E - (FAMOUS FOR HOTDOGS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - FAIRMOUNT BAGEL, LOCATED AT 74 AVENUE FAIRMOUNT O - (FAMOUS FOR BAGEL)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - MONTREAL - {FAMOUS FOR TOURTIERE IS A TYPE OF MEAT PIE MADE FROM PORK, VEAL, BEEF OR FISH}</strong></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(784, 16, 41, 388, 'Qubec', 'Canada', 'QUEBEC CITY', 'habitat-67-2283537_640.jpg', 'habitat-67-2283537_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Quebec City lies on the country&#39;s east coast and play host to some of Canada&#39;s most beautiful countryside. Quebec city is one of the oldest settlements in North America, French speaking and home to the Chateau Frontenac a 19th century hotel that dominates the city&#39;s skyline. One of the more prominent francophonie areas worldwide, Quebec is rich and vibrant, in every sense. Culture, art, adventure, religion, natural beauty and luxury are all found in abundance in Quebec and make it one of the most versatile areas around the world, fit for any tourist. One of the few cities of North America that hasn&rsquo;t yet lost its old-world European charm Quebec is the perfect tourist destination. Its beauty not only lies with its aesthetically pleasing neighbourhoods, lush country, religious and indigenous culture but also in its versatility as a tourist destination there is so much to do, all year round, for everybody. From taking a leisurely stroll around Old Quebec and marvelling at its architecture, to finding oneself in awe of the Montmorency Waterfalls, the tourist has a large range of activities to pursue at Quebec. Culturally, Ole d&#39;Orlans and Wendake offer a refreshing look into the city&rsquo;s history with scenic natural surroundings to delight the eye. Thus, Quebec is filled with gems and is great for a quick getaway and simultaneously, a weeks worth of beautiful experiences and travel.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Quebec has no dearth of accommodation youth and student hostels, hotels, camping grounds, apartments, cabins and these are only the tip of the iceberg. For the tourist on a shoestring budget youth and student hostels are available at cheap prices with many amenities. For the tourist inclined more towards nature, camping grounds or cabins are suitable and for the more urban tourists, hotels and apartments are available. Apartments are a better option for mid range travellers, especially families as they are cheaper than hotel rooms.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Jean-Lesage International Airport that is 10 kms away from the city centre is well connected to all major cities in Canada, USA and around Europe.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Rail Canada facilitates rail travel between important Canadian cities like Ottawa, Montreal, Toronto and Quebec.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Intercar, Orleans Express and Greyhound buses are all available for transport to and from important Canadian cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Highway 20 or Auto route Jean Lesage is the main route to Quebec from almost every Canadian city, and Highway 40 makes the city accessible from the north.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water </strong>- There are ferries across the St. Lawrence River, and that is about the entire waterway that Quebec has.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - The best way to get around the main city of Quebec is to walk. Cycling and motorcycling are also other quicker options. Public transit such as local buses and taxis are also available as are car and limousine rentals.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - QUEBEC CITY - {FAMOUS FOR CRETONS IS MEAT SPREAD MADE FROM PORK, ONIONS, SPICES ; BAKED BEANS (FEVES AU LARD) IS A DISH CONSISTING BEANS AND &nbsp;PORK AND MAPLE SYRUP ; PEA SOUP (SOUPE AUX POIS) IS A SOUP MADE FROM DRY YELLOW PEAS, SALT PORK, AND CARROT ; PIG&#39;S TROTTER STEW (RAGO&ucirc;T DE PATTES DE PORC) IS A STEW MADE FROM &nbsp;PIG&rsquo;S TROTTERS, POTATOES, AND SPICES ; TARTE AU SUCRE(SUGAR PIE) IS A DESERT MADE FROM FLOUR, BUTTER, VANILLA, CREAM}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - CAFE ST-MALO, LOCATED AT 75 RUE SAINT-PAUL - (FAMOUS FOR SEAFOOD SOUP)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - PAILLARD, LOCATED AT 1097 RUE SAINT-JEAN, VILLE DE QUEBEC - (FAMOUS FOR SOUPS, SANDWICHES AND QUICHE IS A &nbsp;PASTRY &nbsp;FILLING &nbsp;WITH EGGS AND MILK OR CREAM, CHEESE, MEAT, SEAFOOD OR VEGETABLES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(785, 16, 41, 387, 'Ontario', 'Canada', 'OTTAWA', 'canada-1607114_640.jpg', 'canada-1607114_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Ottawa is Canada&rsquo;s capital a dynamic city steeped in culture with world class museums displaying stunning national collections and special exhibitions from around the world. For a capital city, Ottawa is small and friendly and nowhere near the size of counterparts Toronto and Montreal. The city is charming and bike friendly, peaceful and civilised, and a great base for exploring the Canadian wilderness on its doorstep in Ontario. Draped in natural splendour and brimming with a relaxed urban vibe, Ottawa is a truly unique destination offering a wealth of experiences visitors won&rsquo;t find anywhere else, including Ontario&rsquo;s only UNESCO World Heritage Site, the Rideau Canal. Canada&rsquo;s capital and Ontario&rsquo;s second largest city is a showcase of national sites, monuments, museums and the arts where visitors can experience the best of our country in one place. Ottawa&#39;s charming countryside offers natural beauty and an abundance of quaint shops. Ottawa is filled with national sites and attractions perfect for a getaway. Canada&rsquo;s stylish capital Ottawa is a city rich in arts, heritage and sciences. The city blends ultra modern and Victorian Gothic architecture balances technology with nature and offers cuisines from across the globe. Come and enjoy Ottawa this summer and take in a unique Sound and Light Show that is set against the backdrop of the beautiful Parliament Buildings.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">One of the most advantageous aspects about Ottawa&#39;s hotels is that they come in all shapes and sizes. Whether looking to stay in a centuries old stone building or a modern boutique designer gem along the water, one has got options. Many of the city&#39;s hotels are clustered in the centre, thus making it convenient to walk pretty much anywhere. There are several excellent choices however slightly outside the downtown core.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\n<strong>By Air </strong>- The newly renovated and expanded Macdonald-Cartier International Airport is Ottawa&#39;s main airport with regular arrivals and departures from most major Canadian and many American cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Passenger train service is run by Via Rail in Canada and the main train station in Ottawa is less than ten minutes from downtown by car, taxi or bus. There are six trains daily leaving for Montreal and intermediate points.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- There is a Voyageur/Greyhound terminal in Ottawa with regular service to Montreal, Toronto and all other cities in North America. The bus terminal is downtown on the corner of Catherine Street and Kent Street, between Bronson Avenue and Bank Street.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water </strong>- The city is also accessible via the Rideau Canal, now recognized by UNESCO as a World Heritage site, and which runs from the St. Lawrence River at Kingston to the Ottawa River at Ottawa where it empties via a series of locks.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around </strong>- The city&#39;s public transit is run by OC Transpo and includes the bus service as well as the O-Train light rail system. Taxis are easy to find downtown and parking at most attractions is convenient, though on-street parking in downtown areas is sometimes at a premium. Ottawa is also a great city to explore on foot and there are few options for renting bicycles downtown.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - BITE BURGER HOUSE, LOCATED AT 108 MURRAY ST - (FAMOUS FOR BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - FOOLISH CHICKEN, LOCATED AT 79 HOLLAND AVE - (FAMOUS FOR ROASTED CHICKEN AND CHEESECAKES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - FRITOMANIA, LOCATED AT 2442 ST JOSEPH BLVD, ORLEANS - (FAMOUS FOR POUTINE &nbsp;IS A DISH MADE FROM &nbsp;FRENCH FRIES, GRAVY, CHEESE CURDS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - OH SO GOOD DESSERTS &amp; COFFEE HOUSE, LOCATED AT 261 RICHMOND ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR CAKES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - AD MARE SEAFOOD TRUCK, LOCATED AT 150 SLATER ST - (FAMOUS FOR LOBSTER ROLL)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n6 - MEZZANOTTE BISTRO, LOCATED AT 50 MURRAY ST - (FAMOUS FOR SEAFOOD PASTA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - TENNESSY WILLEMS, LOCATED AT 1082 WELLINGTON ST, W - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;PIZZA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - FLAPJACK&#39;S CANADIAN DINER, LOCATED AT 354A PRESTON ST - (FAMOUS FOR PANCAKES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>9 - MERIVALE, LOCATED AT 1480 MERIVALE RD, NEPEAN - (FAMOUS FOR FISH AND CHIPS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n10 - BAKER STREET CAFE, LOCATED AT 385 RICHMOND ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR EGGS BENEDICT IS A BREAKFAST DISH MADE FROM EGGS, MUFFIN, BACON AND HOLLANDAISE SAUCE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>11 - BURRITO BORRACHO, LOCATED AT 105A CLARENCE ST - (FAMOUS FOR CHURRO IS A TYPE OF FRIED DOUGH PASTRY MADE FROM &nbsp;FLOUR)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>12 - DATSUN, LOCATED AT 380 ELGIN ST - {FAMOUS FOR BAO IS A TYPE OF STEAMED BREAD, FILLED BUN OR BREAD-LIKE ( MADE WITH YEAST)}<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n13 - HINTONBURGER, LOCATED AT 1066 SOMERSET ST W - (FAMOUS FOR BURGERS AND SWEET POTATO FRIES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>14 - LA PATATERIE HULLOISE, LOCATED AT 311 BOULEVARD SAINT-JOSEPH, GATINEAU - (FAMOUS FOR CHEESEBURGER AND FRIED ZUCCHINI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(786, 16, 41, 383, 'British Colombia', 'Canada', 'VICTORIA', 'lion-1606803_1280.jpg', 'lion-1606803_12801.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Victoria, British Columbia is the capital of Canada&rsquo;s third most populated province. Named after Britain&rsquo;s and Canada&rsquo;s most famous 19th century queen, the city is situated on the south eastern tip of Vancouver Island. Renowned for its mild weather and bounteous and early springs, Victoria boasts gorgeous gardens and a multicultural heritage that goes back generations. Victoria boasts many historic buildings and some of the best museums in Western Canada. The area is also home to some of the country&#39;s most exhilarating scenery there&#39;s an ocean or mountain vista around every corner and the city&#39;s flower gardens are famous the world over. Established in 1843 as a fort for the Hudson&#39;s Bay Company, Victoria&#39;s British ancestry is apparent in the double-decker buses, horse drawn carriages, formal gardens and tearooms. The city is now a cosmopolitan centre with a lively entertainment scene and a wonderful array of attractions. As the province&rsquo;s capital, the Parliament buildings are worth a visit. Much of the parks, museums, galleries and gardens are all within walking distance within the city centre. Exploring outside of the city limits will bring fruitful adventures that are picture worthy and memorable.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Victoria is a charming city on the water that&rsquo;s accessible from Vancouver by ferry. Much of the city is within walking distance and one will find the majority of hotels in the city centre. From indulgent luxury to affordable convenience, Victoria has everything for to rest the weary head. Even not staying at the Fairmont Empress in James Bay, it&#39;s worth a visit. Enjoy views of Parliament buildings, crisp ocean waters and beautiful mountains beyond the water.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The Victoria International Airport operates just 30 minutes away, while floatplanes and helicopters constantly fly in and out of the downtown harbour during daylight hours.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- Pacific Coach and Greyhound Canada provides scheduled services and sightseeing bus tours between Vancouver and downtown Victoria via BC Ferries, with several pick up and drop off points in route. Tofino Bus Services offers daily scheduled service linking Victoria with Nanaimo, Parksville, Port Alberni, Ucluelet and Tofino.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water</strong> - BC Ferries is the primary provider of coastal ferry service in the province and it is one of the most sophisticated ferry transportation systems in the world. The company provides scheduled vehicle and passenger services between Tsawwassen and Swartz Bay.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Victoria is connected to Nanaimo and other northern points by the Trans-Canada Hwy-1. BC-4 connects Victoria to Sooke and Port Renfrew. BC-17 connects Sidney to Victoria.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - There are several ways to get around Victoria, but walking and cycling are the best options. There are many safe, car free paths in the city, some of which connect to long country trails. If going farther afield along a scenic driving route or prefer to drive there are plenty of car rental companies to choose from. The neighbouring Gulf Islands are just a scenic ferry ride away.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(787, 16, 41, 382, 'Alberta', 'Canada', 'EDMONTON', 'edmonton-174104_640.jpg', 'edmonton-174104_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Edmonton is a historic Canadian city located on the North Saskatchewan River in Alberta. The destination offers something for everyone, Fort Edmonton Park for history buffs, the Art Gallery of Alberta for art lovers, the TELUS World of Science for science fans and Winspear Centre for music enthusiasts. Known for its natural beauty, culture, history and attractions, Edmonton is a city for everyone. It is home to Canada&rsquo;s largest living history museum, Canada&rsquo;s largest historical park and North America&rsquo;s largest mall. It is also has a vibrant theatre scene, numerous professional sports teams and some stunning architecture. There is something to please everyone in Edmonton, from outdoor recreational activities to indoor fun. Shopping, dining, hiking, skating and even skiing are all offered in the city, making it one of Canada&rsquo;s top tourist destinations. Edmonton boasts many cultural attractions and historic landmarks. Visit Fort Edmonton, the largest living history museum in Canada, or the Royal Alberta Museum to view the cultural and natural history collections. Edmonton is also known as &lsquo;Festival City&rsquo; because of its many world class festivals held throughout the year, from the Works Art and Design Festival in spring to the International Fringe Festival in summer to Ice on Whyte in winter. Edmonton is also home to beautiful gardens, neighbourhoods and parks which one can explore on its own or with the help of a local tour guide.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The best accommodations in Edmonton are found in its bustling downtown, in the historic Old Strathcona neighbourhood or near the world famous West Edmonton Mall. Downtown hotels offer convenience for business travellers and close proximity to some great restaurants, shopping and nightlife. Adjacent to the University of Alberta, Old Strathcona is Edmonton&rsquo;s trendiest neighbourhood. Hotels here are within walking distance to eclectic eateries, fashionable shops and the best live music venues in the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Edmonton International is located 10 kms south of Edmonton in Leduc County. Edmonton International Airport is the fastest growing large airport in Canada with parking services, terminals, planes and shops.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Via Rail provides passenger train services for Edmonton and is linked to several major cities along the Canadian National Railroad west to Vancouver and east to Saskatoon, Winnipeg, Toronto, and Montreal and onwards.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- Greyhound buses service Edmonton from all major Canadian cities. There is also a premium service between Edmonton and Calgary. Executive Express runs a daily scheduled service from Calgary to Edmonton departing Calgary in the morning and returning to Calgary in the Afternoon.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Known as Gateway to the North, Edmonton is the largest city on the Alberta Highway 16 of the Trans-Canada Highway system. Edmonton is 3 hours north of Calgary on the divided Highway 2 and 3.5 hours east of Jasper on Highway 16. From Vancouver, Edmonton is best accessed using Highway 1 east to Hope, then Highway 5 from Hope to the Highway 16 eastbound junction.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - A large part of the city built before and during the Second World War is laid out in a grid pattern of straight streets which makes for easy navigation by car or foot. There are a number of bridges including the Walterdale Bridge and High Level Bridge going in and out of the downtown core. All Edmonton taxi companies offer 24/7 service. Edmonton has a safe, efficient and inexpensive public transportation system the Edmonton Transit System.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - LOCAL PUBLIC EATERY, LOCATED AT 1820 99 ST, NW &nbsp;- (FAMOUS FOR BURGER AND STEAK SANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - SUGARBOWL, LOCATED AT 10922 88TH AVENUE - (FAMOUS FOR OMELETTES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - THE COMMON, LOCATED AT &nbsp;9910 109 ST - (FAMOUS FOR CORNED BEEF AND CHICKEN AND WAFFLES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - NORMANDS RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT 11639 JASPER AVE - (FAMOUS FOR WILD MUSHROOM SOUP)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n5 - PACKRAT LOUIE KITCHEN &amp; BAR, LOCATED AT 10335 83 AVE NW - (FAMOUS FOR LEMON PIZZA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - DADEO, LOCATED AT 10548A WHYTE AVENUE - {FAMOUS FOR PULLED PORK (SMOTHERED IN TANGY BBQ SAUCE WITH DIJON MAYO AND LETTUCE) AND FRIED OYSTERS (WITH HERB MAYO, LETTUCE, AND TOMATO)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - URBAN DINER, LOCATED AT &nbsp;12427 102 AVE NW - (FAMOUS FOR FRENCH TOAST, CHOCOLATE CHEESECAKE &amp; SANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - BLUE PLATE DINER, LOCATED AT 10145 104 ST NW - (FAMOUS FOR BURGER)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n9 - MEININGFUL, FUSION RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT 10338 81 AVE NW - (FAMOUS FOR LAKSA IS A SOUP MADE FROM &nbsp;NOODLES OR RICE VERMICELLI, COCONUT MILK, CURRY SOUP BASE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>10 - THREE BOARS EATERY, LOCATED AT 8424 109 ST NW &nbsp;- (FAMOUS FOR MUSHROOMS WITH EGG YOLK)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>11 - CIBO BISTRO, LOCATED AT 11244 104 AVE NW - (FAMOUS FOR ARANCINI IS A SNACK MADE FROM &nbsp;RICE, MEAT COATED WITH BREAD CRUMBS THEN FRIED, FILLED WITH RAGU (MEAT AND TOMATO SAUCE), CHEESE, AND PEAS</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>12 - JACK&#39;S BURGER SHACK, LOCATED AT 15 PERRON ST #130, ST ALBERT - (FAMOUS FOR MILKSHAKES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>13 - ELM CAFE, LOCATED AT 10140 117 ST NW - (FAMOUS FOR SANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>14 - THE LOCAL OMNIVORE, LOCATED AT 10933 120 ST - (FAMOUS FOR BACON AND EGG SANDWICH)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>15 - &nbsp;SUGARED AND SPICE, LOCATED AT 10334 82 AVE NW - (FAMOUS FOR PEANUT BUTTER, CHOCOLATE CHIP AND BACON COOKIE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>16 - COOKIE LOVE, LOCATED AT 10235 101 STREET #142 - (FAMOUS FOR BLACK AND WHITE CHEESECAKE COOKIE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>17 - SHANGHAI 456, LOCATED AT 14456 118 AVE NW - {FAMOUS FOR XIAO LONG BAO (STEAMED PORK BUNS) AND WOR TIP (FRIED BEEF DUMPLINGS)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>18 - ROUTE 99 DINER, LOCATED AT 8820 99 ST NW - (FAMOUS FOR FRENCH TOAST WITH SAUSAGE)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n19 - DE DUTCH, LOCATED AT 10030 JASPER AVE - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;PANCAKES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(788, 19, 93, 1855, 'lle de France', 'France', 'PARIS', 'paris-1836415_640.jpg', 'paris-1836415_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Paris is the capital city of France as well as its most populous one. Being the third most visited city in the world, there are lots of things to do in Paris. Founded in the 3rd Century BC, Paris is best known as the home to various most visited museums in the world. Going to this city is such a great pleasure especially if one likes the romantic walks through old streets and seeing some of the greatest architectural treasures. However it is not as easy as Paris is quite large, so prepare comfortable shoes and reserve few days for it. As a French capital, Paris is the undisputed homeland of museums and universities, haute couture and luxury, good food and romanticism. Paris is one of the greatest art repositories in the world harbouring artistic pedigree in the likes of Renoir, Rodin, Picasso, Monet and Van Gogh. The magnificent Louvre, exceptional impressionist collections and the Centre Pompidou&#39;s modern and contemporary art, a plethora of smaller museums showcasing collections in every genre imaginable. The mesmerizing wrought iron spire of the Eiffel Tower piercing the skyline, the Arc de Triomphe guarding the most glamorous avenue, the Champs Elysees, the regal Notre Dame cathedral, lamp lit bridges spanning the Seine and art nouveau cafes spilling on to wicker chair lined terraces.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Paris caters to travellers with accommodation options in all price ranges. While the Right Bank hosts the luxury hotels, the Left Bank is home to the budget hotels laden with old fashioned charm. Paris hotels range from comfortable to utterly fabulous. Stay in the city centre to be nearest to the top attractions. Tourists won&#39;t be able to be right by them all, so take comfort in the fact that Paris has an efficient metro system. Keep in mind that the Left Bank is historically artsy around the Bastille.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Paris can be accessed by two main international airports Roissy Charles de Gaulle, around 30 kms away from the city and Orly Airport which is around 20 kms from the city. Beauvais Airport is served by low cost airlines operating from Barcelona, Madrid, Alicante, Budapest and other nearby cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Train travel is viable from cities in France and all other major European cities. Railway stations in Paris are centrally located and each with specific destinations, they offer smooth connections with the public transport network.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - With an excellent national train service in place, the need for buses is sparse. Buses operate regionally, particularly in places train service where is erratic. Local bus information can be obtained from the SNCF.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Depending on where coming in from one will join the ring road at one of the 30 gateways that punctuate the 35 kms expressway. The major ring road encircling Paris gives the choice between the inner ring road which runs in a clockwise direction and the outer which runs anti clockwise.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water</strong> - Ferries link Port D&#39;Larsenal, Paris to United Kingdom in about 1.5 hrs. The most popular route is between Calais and Dover while others include Boulogne and Folkestone, Le Havre and Portsmouth.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - Paris has an extremely organised and well connected public transport system. One would rarely need to haul a taxi, since the transport facilities are constructed keeping in mind the various places of attractions and sights. This romantic city can also be well explored on foot and is increasingly bike friendly, with cycling lanes.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - PARIS - {FAMOUS FOR JAMBON-BEURRE IS A SANDWICH MADE FROM BAGUETTE( BREAD MADE FROM FLOUR, WATER AND YEAST), WITH BUTTER AND HAM (PORK) ; &nbsp;STEAK FRITES IS A POPULAR DISH MADE FROM STEAK, POTATOES AND VARIOUS SAUCES ; CROQUE-MONSIEUR IS A TYPE OF SANDWICH MADE FROM EGGS, BUTTER,BOILLED HAM(PORK), CHEESE AND BREAD ; &nbsp;PARIS- BREAST IS A DESERT MADE FROM CHOUX PASTRY AND A PRALINE CREAM &nbsp;; MACAROON IS A TYPE OF CAKEMADE FROM ALMONDS, COCONUT WITH SUGAR AND EGG WHITE ; POT-AU-FEUoIS A BEEF DISH MADE FROM VEGETABLES ,MEAT OF OX ; &nbsp;A CROQUE-MONSIEUR OR CROQUE MADAME IS A SANDWICH MADE FROM CHEESE HAM}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - ALLARD , LOCATED AT 41 RUE SAINT-ANDRE DES ARTS - (FAMOUS FOR EGGS WITH MUSHROOMS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - AU PIED DE COCHON, LOCATED AT 6 RUE COQUILLERE - (FAMOUS FOR ROASTED CHICKEN &nbsp;AND ONION SOUP)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - BISTROT, LOCATED AT 18 RUE PAUL BERT - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;BUTTERY MONKFISH WITH MUSHROOM)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - CAFE CONSTANT, LOCATED AT 139 RUE SAINT- DOMINIQUE - (FAMOUS FOR BUTTER CHICKEN AND GRILLED FISH WITH RATATOUILLE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - FRENCHIE TO GO, LOCATED AT 9 RUE DU NIL - (FAMOUS FOR PASTARAMI (MEAT) SANDWICH, FISH &lsquo;N&rsquo; CHIPS, LOBOSTER ROLL AND HOTDOG)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - CHEZ MICHEL, LOCATED AT 10 RUE DE BELZUNCE - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;CHOUX PASTRY FILLED PRALINE MOUSEE AND GARNISHED WITH &nbsp;NUTS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - ABRI, LOCATED AT 92 RUE DU FAUBOURG POISSONNIERE - (FAMOUS FOR PORK SANDWICH)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>9 - ZERDA CAFE, LOCATED AT 15 RUE RENE BOULANGER - (FAMOUS FOR COUSCOUS IS A DISH MADE FROM SEMOLINA)</s