>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>20 - LA BOURSE ET LA VIE, LOCATED AT 12 RUE &nbsp;VIVIENNE - (FAMOUS FOR FOIE GRAS IS A FOOD MADE FROM THE LIVER OF A DUCK OR GOOSE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>21 - A. NOSTE, LOCATED AT 6 RUE DU &nbsp;4 SEPTEMBRE - (FAMOUS FOR TALO IS ATYPE OF BREAD MADE FROM CORN FLOUR)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>22 - NOSSA CHURRASQUEIRA, LOCATED AT 1 RUE DE l&#39;ECOLE POLYTECHNIQUE - (FAMOUS FOR ROASTED CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>23 - CAFE TRAMA, LOCATED AT 83 RUE DU CHERCHE-MIDI - (FAMOUS FOR CROQUE MONSIEUR &nbsp;IS A TYPE OF SANDWICH MADE FROM HAM(PORK), CHEESE WITH EGGS AND BREAD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>24 - JOSEPHINE CHEZ &nbsp;DUMONET, LOCATED AT 117 RUE DU CHERCHE-MIDI - (FAMOUS FOR BOEUF BOURGUIGNON IS A TYPE OF &nbsp;DISH MADE FROM BEEF, RED WINE, ONIONS AND MUSHROOMS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>25 - LE DUC, LOCATED AT 243 BOULEVARD RASPAIL - (&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;FAMOUS FOR SOLE MEUNIERE &nbsp;IS FISH DISH)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>26 - LE SEVERO, LOCATED AT 8 RUE DES PLANTES - (FAMOUS FOR STEAK TARTARE IS A MEAT DISH MADE FROM RAW BEEF OR HORSEMEAT)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>27 - JOE, &nbsp;LOCATED AT 49 RUE DESCARTES - (FAMOUS FOR BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>28 - MOBSTER DINER, LOCATED AT 20 RUE DES BOULANGERS - (FAMOUS FOR HAMBURGERS)</strong></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(789, 19, 93, 1854, 'Provence AlpesCote dAzur', 'France', 'NICE', 'nice-1818378_640.jpg', 'nice-1818378_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Located on the scenic south coast of France with panoramic views across the Mediterranean Sea, Nice has become one of the most popular tourist spots in the country. Nestled between mountains, azure blue sea and Provencal countryside Nice is an eternal source of inspiration for its guests whether they are passing through or long-time residents. From its old fashioned houses to its elegant buildings, Nice serves a salad deliciously seasoned with discoveries. Its products and culinary traditions sumptuously garnish this picture. Famous for its belle &eacute;poque architecture, Nice is quite definitely one of the liveliest cities in the south of France and has all the benefits of being a cosmopolitan town, a great seaside resort and enjoying the influence of nearby Italian and Mediterranean cultures. Nice has been attracting tourists for at least the last two centuries to enjoy its lovely coastline and soak up its wonderful culture. It may lack the glamour of nearby Cannes or Monaco but is the entire better for that remaining with its feet firmly fixed on the ground and offering an all round fantastic experience for the visitor or the resident. Built upon the graceful curve of the Bay of Angels Nice is one of France&#39;s great cities with palm lined boulevards, beautiful architecture and a melting pot of cultures and cuisines.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Hotels in Nice range from budget youth hostels and guest houses to luxury four star hotels, like the seafront Palais de la Mediterranee. Youth hostels offer dorm style and private rooms, though several are located further away from the heart of the city. Smaller guest houses range from small hotels to bed and breakfasts. The cosmopolitan seaside city of Nice has a wealth of accommodation to suit all of your holiday aspirations. It is a well known conference city, so there are plenty of hotels to choose from whether looking to stay in the heart of the action or prefer a more peaceful location in the hills, Nice has everything.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- The closest airport is Nice Cote d&#39;Azur Airport, situated just 8 kms away from the city centre and is serviced by a number of the major airlines.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Nice is connected to the rest of France via the SNCF train network. The TGV, France&#39;s intercity high speed rail service, runs directly from Paris to Nice and takes approximately 6 hrs. Trenitalia train service connects Nice to Italian cities like Milan, Genoa, Rome and Venice.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- Long distance buses connect Nice with other major European cities. Eurolines and the French Lignes Express Regionaux connect Nice with Marseille, Toulon and Aixen Provence at a reasonable price and acceptable three hour journey time via the motorways.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water</strong> - Nice has direct ferry routes to Ajaccio, Bastia, Calvi and Ile Rousse. However, remember to contact the local port before arrival to reserve a place for the boat. Advance booking is advised in all cases. Nice is right along the coast and it&rsquo;s easy to it by boat.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - Nice has an excellent and cheap public transport network with a new and modern tram system as well as buses and trains connecting Nice with the rest of the Cote d&#39;Azur. Each main town on the French Riviera has its own local bus network.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - NICE - {FAMOUS FOR SOCCA IS A TYPE OF PANCAKE MADE FROM CHICKPEA FLOUR AND OLIVE OIL ; SALADE NICOISE &nbsp;IS A TYPE OF SALAD MADE FROM TOMATOES AND EGG ; PAIN BAGNAT IS A TYPE OF SANDWICH Made From Pain de campagne or round white bread, Ni&ccedil;oise salad (radishes, tomatoes, pepper, onion, hard-boiled egg, olives, anchovies, olive oil) ; RATATOUILLE IS A TYPE OF DISH MADE FROM VEGETABLES LIKE, (TOMATOES. ONIONS, ZUCCHINI, EGGPLANT) BELL PEPEERS, GARLIC, AND BASIL(HERB) ; &nbsp;PISTOU IS A SOUP MADE FROM GARLIC, BASIL(HERB) AND OLIVE OIL ; PISSALADIERE &nbsp;IS A DISH MADE FROM BREAD DOUGH, ONIONS, OLIVES, GARLIC}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - LE SAFARI, LOCATED AT&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;1 COURS SALEYA - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA AND FISH DISHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - LOU PILHA LEVA, LOCATED AT &nbsp;10 RUE DU COLLET - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN AND CHIPS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - TACA D&#39;OLI, LOCATED AT 35 RUE PAIROLIERE - (FAMOUS FOR FISH SOUP)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - LAFRITKOT, LOCATED AT 39 AVENUE GEORGES CLEMENCEAU - (FAMOUS FOR MOULES-FRITES IS A DISH MADE FROM POTATES, MUSSELS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - LA PICCOLA CAPRI, LOCATED AT 16 RUE DELILLE - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - 5TH AVENUE, LOCATED AT 41 RUE BONAPARTE - (FAMOUS FOR HOTDOGS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - SMART DELIGHT ROOM, LOCATED AT 31 RUE GIOFFREDO - (FAMOUS FOR BURGERS AND SANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>9 - TANDOORI FLAME, LOCATED AT 1 RUE CENTRALE - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKENPAKORA, CHICKEN CURRY AND KEBABS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>10 - BRASILIA A CAFE, LOCATED AT 8 RUE BONAPARTE&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; - (FAMOUS FOR FRUIT JUICES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>11 - CHEZ MAITRE PIERRE, LOCATED AT 41 RUE MASSENA - (FAMOUS FOR PASTRIES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>12 - CO-T-CAFE, LOCATED AT 11 RUE MEYERBEER - (FAMOUS FOR COFFEE AND SANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>13 - CHEZ MOI, &nbsp;LOCATED AT 6 RUE PAGANINI - (FAMOUS FOR ROASTED CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>14 - PHO PAGANINI, LOCATED AT &nbsp;20 RUE PAGANINI - (FAMOUS FOR SPRINGSROLLS AND BEEF NOODLES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>15 - CAFE MERCIER, LOCATED AT 17 RUE DE LA LIBERTE - (FAMOUS FOR BURGERS, PASTA AND PASTRIES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(790, 19, 93, 1853, 'Rhone Alpes', 'France', 'LYON', 'lyon-1273841_640.jpg', 'lyon-1273841_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Situated at the crossroads of Europe, two hours from the ski resorts of the Alps and just a little further to the Mediterranean, Lyon&rsquo;s history, architecture, culture and culinary delights are more than worthy of a tour on the way to the sun or the slopes. In fact, the city itself is now a major attraction, whether it&rsquo;s pleasure loving music festivals, fine dining or lashings of history and architecture. A UNESCO world heritage site, Lyon&rsquo;s major selling point for many visitors are its distinctive architectural hallmarks and the contrasts in its setting, between two hills and two rivers. Its centre is beautiful and it&rsquo;s enough to have snapping selfies all over the place. The riverfront is being transformed under an ambitious, six year plan to develop 48 kms of former docks. The Confluence project is now Europe&rsquo;s largest single urban regeneration mission and it include open-air cafes, promenades, viewing points, art installations and galleries as well as nature trails, museums, a huge shopping mall, tram lines and eccentric apartment blocks built like Lego houses in primary colours and blocky shapes. Lyon itself has a mixed heritage, displaying traits of a typical northern French town in some areas, while other features bear witness to its Latin origins. Lyon&rsquo;s history of resistance during WWII, of being the cradle of the invention of film and cinema of its artists, architects and musicians these all give it a highly cultured and intriguing feel. With outstanding art museums, fantastic shopping and a thriving nightlife, Lyon has become a cultural and dynamic city with plenty to offer.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Lyon&rsquo;s nine districts surround the two major rivers running through the city the Rhone and the Saone. The most scenic districts are Vieux Lyon and La Croix Rousse, where the city&rsquo;s historic sites are located. Lodging in these areas is walking distance to these sites. Near the breathtaking Parc de la Tete, the Tete D&rsquo;Or district offers a quieter option away from the city centre.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Lyon&#39;s Saint-Exupery Airport, some 25 kms east of Lyon is a rapidly developing airport. It hosts few intercontinental flights but can easily be reached via a European hub.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Lyon has three main train stations serving national and regional destinations. Lyon is linked by TGV to Paris and Marseille. Many other domestic destinations are served directly and there are several direct services to Brussels every day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- International bus services are operated by Eurolines to and from Perrache station, Lyon.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around </strong>- The Metro network in Lyon is excellent. It&rsquo;s clean and easy to use, with four different lines and 40 stations crossing the city. The central bus station is based at Lyon Perrache railway station. It is possible to hail taxis in the street or from taxi ranks. The centre of Lyon is best explored on foot. Nevertheless, driving in Lyon is not as bad as it is in some other French cities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - LYON&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; - (FAMOUS FOR ANDOUILLE IS A SAUSAGE MADE FROM PORK)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - CAFE COMPTOIR ABEL, LOCATED AT 26 RUE GUYNEMER - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN WITH MUSHROOM SAUCE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - LE GARET, LOCATED AT 7 RUE DU GARET - (FAMOUS FOR SAUCISSON &nbsp;IS A DRY CURED SAUSAGE MADE OF PORK AND ROASTED POTATOES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - LE POELON D&#39;OR, LOCATED AT 29 RUE DES REMPARTS D&#39;AINAY - (FAMOUS FOR QUENELLE IS A DISH MADE 0F A MIXTURE OF CREAMED FISH OR MEAT)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n5 - THE CROK&#39;N&#39;ROLL (ST PAUL), LOCATED AT 6 &nbsp;RUE OCTAVIO MEY - (FAMOUS FOR SANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - SLAKE COFFEE HOUSE, LOCATED AT 9 RUE DE &nbsp;l&#39;ANCIENNE PREFECTURE - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;CHOCOLATE COOKIE AND COFFEE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - L&#39;EPICERIE, LOCATED AT 2 RUE DE LA MONNAIE - (FAMOUS FOR VARITIES OF SOUPS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - YAAFA, LOCATED AT 17 RUE D&#39;ALGERIE - (FAMOUS FOR FALAFELIS A DOUGHNUT OR PATTY MADE FROM CHICKPEAS AND FAVA BEANS)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n9 - TANDOOR LYON, LOCATED AT 32 RUE DE MARSEILLE - (FAMOUS FOR PANEER PAKORA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>10 - GOURMIX, LOCATED AT 22 RUE DE LA PLATIERE - (FAMOUS FOR SANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>11 - PUZZLE CAFE, &nbsp;LOCATED AT 4 RUE DE LA &nbsp;POULAILLERE - (FAMOUS FOR CARROT CAKE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>12 - HOT-GLOBE, LOCATED AT 28 RUE NEUVE - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;HOTDOGS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>13 - STREET ART, &nbsp;LOCATED AT 73 RUE MASSENA - (FAMOUS FOR BURGERS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>14 - TANDOOR TIME, LOCATED AT 27 RUE DES &nbsp;CHARMETTES - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN TIKKA MASALA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>15 - NAM, LOCATED AT 12 PLACE RASPAIL - (FAMOUS FOR BUTTER CHICKEN WITH CURRY SAUCE)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', '');
