(800, 19, 94, 1844, 'Greater Manchester', 'United Kingdom', 'MANCHESTER', 'bridge-2231612_640.jpg', 'bridge-2231612_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Manchester is England&rsquo;s second biggest city, having been settled since 79 AD by the Romans. Manchester is a vibrant urban hotspot with excellent nightlife, arts and culture. The city is surrounded by countryside and the gorgeous Pennine Mountains, making it a great base for exploring wilder regions of the country. Manchester has an extensive history and is important in many fields, including music, science and transport. It is home to the world&rsquo;s first intercity passenger railway station and a thriving culture scene, making it one of England&rsquo;s most exciting cities. Manchester the cultural hub of Britain is a city that is thriving with music festivals art exhibitions and food festivals. Manchester is a cosmopolitan city and home to people of different races and ethnicities. It is a melting pot of various cultures from around the world. When in Manchester, do not miss to visit the various art galleries and museums. Manchester city gets into the festive mood during the festive seasons from March to August. The winter season is lined up with many fun filled festivals. There is also the National Winter Ales Festival usually held in the month of January. Lying in the heart of Greater Manchester, Manchester is a city in the North-western part of England. It is known for its impact on the historical scenario of industry and music as well as famous for its football clubs. It is a vibrant city visited by numerous tourists all around the year. Manchester is one of those cities in Central United Kingdom which played a great role during the Industrial Revolution.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The city centre in Manchester is filled with the five star and four star hotels that are elegant and luxurious while the outskirts of Manchester have affordable guesthouses, small hotels and Motels. The ones situated in the outskirts are cheaper and best suited for the budget travellers. There are also options for hostel accommodation under YHA Manchester and Hilton Chambers. Manchester&#39;s centrally located hotels boast modern rooms, good food and friendly staff. From there one can easily explore Manchester&#39;s famous pubs, rooftop bars and restaurants.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - The central coach station in Manchester is Chorlton Street Coach Station which is located between Chinatown and the Village, close to the centre of the city. There are buses from all over the country and it is the most reasonable way of transportation to Manchester.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Flight</strong> - The Manchester Airport is situated in the southern part of the city and is the largest airport in UK, apart from London. It is among the 50 largest airports in the world and almost 100 operators fly to and from multiple locations around the world.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail</strong> - There are two main railway stations in Manchester Victoria in the north and Piccadilly in the south. Piccadilly is the main station for long distance trains from around UK as well as some local services, whereas Victoria is predominantly for local stopping trains from Lancashire and Liverpool.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - The transport in Manchester in coordinated by Tf-Gm and it sells a number of tickets which are valid for multiple operators. Hiring a car or cab from the rental agencies is another mode of commotion in Manchester. Manchester also has one of the best modern tram networks in the world and they are more economical than any other means of transport. Exploring the city centre can be done on foot.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - DOUGH &amp; APOTHECA, LOCATED AT 77 HIGH ST. - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA &nbsp;AND PASTA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - JAFFA RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT 185 WILMSLOW ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR FATAYER IS A TYPE OF MEAT PIE MADE FROM MEAT, SPINACH OR CHEESE OR ZAATAR)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - DOGS N DOUGH, LOCATED AT 17 BOW LN - (FAMOUS FOR HOTDOGS SAND PIZZA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - AL JAZEERA, LOCATED AT 22 WILMSLOW ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR ROASTED CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - GO FALAFEL, LOCATED AT 3 NEWTON ST. - (FAMOUS FOR FALAFEL WRAPS, HUMMUS(IS A SPREAD MADE FROM CHICKPEAS OR OTHER BEANS, BLENDED WITH TAHINI, OLIVE OIL, LEMON JUICE, SALT AND GARLIC) AND JUICES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - VIET SHACK, LOCATED AT 49 HIGH ST. - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN BURGER AND SPICED LAMB CHOPS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - HAPPY SEASONS RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT 59 FAULKNER ST. - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN WINGS, SPRING ROLLS AND SLICED PORK &nbsp;VEGETABLE SOUP)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - HOME SWEET HOME, LOCATED AT 49-51 EDGE ST. - (FAMOUS FOR MILKSHAKES AND COFFEE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>9 - TEACUP KITCHEN, LOCATED AT 53-55 THOMAS ST. - (FAMOUS FOR CAKES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>10 - RED&#39;S TRUE BARBECUE, LOCATED AT 22 LLOYD ST. - (FAMOUS FOR CHEESEBURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>11 - LITTLE ALADDIN, LOCATED AT 72 HIGH ST. - (FAMOUS FOR KEBABS AND CURRIES)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n12 - ESSY&#39;S, LOCATED AT 33 KING ST., W. - (FAMOUS FOR SANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>13 - CHENNAI DOSA, LOCATED AT 303-305 PALATINE ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR SOUTH INDIAN FOOD)</strong></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(801, 19, 94, 1843, 'Scotland', 'United Kingdom', 'GLASGOW', 'glasgow-2423346_640.jpg', 'glasgow-2423346_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">An old, historic city that was once part of many important events in the United Kingdom and currently its third largest urban agglomeration, Glasgow is an important commercial centre not just for Scotland but all of the UK as well. It is a port city that is situated on the River Clyde in the western Lowlands of Scotland and mainly famed for Victorian era architecture and as a national cultural hub. Growing to its peak during the British Empire as a river trading port, Glasgow was the epicentre of shipbuilding in its heyday, which lasted until the early 20th century. It was also an important trading port since ancient times for the transatlantic trade route to the West Indies and North America during the late 17th to 19th centuries. The Glasgow University was set up here in the 15th century, resulting in the city becoming a hub for education and learning as well. A city with many medieval cathedrals, modern opera centres, various museums and a prevalent love for football there are many cultural activities and landmarks which it is famous for. Glasgow hosts music and comedy centric festivals, theatrical performances, cultural fairs and many others. This city also has many literary activities as well as universities and is one of the literature capitals of the UK. Glasgow is the largest city in Scotland and is well known for its culture, style and the nature of the people. It is home to numerous internationally famous museums and galleries and boasts a beautiful architecture. The city has a vibrant nightlife and a perfect destination for shopping and food lovers. There is a year round buzz going on in the city and have a lot of exhibitions.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Glasgow offers a wide range of places for staying among which some are extremely classy and luxurious hotels while some are the ones which suit everyone&#39;s budgets. The best options here are the bed and breakfast facilities and most of the tourists choose this thing as it is really very comfortable. Apart from that, two local universities, Strathclyde University and Glasgow University let out the student rooms during Summer Vacation. Considered one of the finest Victorian cities in Britain, Glasgow is renowned for its centrally located hotels.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - There are long distances as well as short distance buses that connect other cities to Glasgow and all these buses arrive at the Buchanan Bus Station. The bus station lies in the centre of the city close to the Queen Street train station and Buchanan Street.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Glasgow is well connected by road to other parts of Europe. The main approaches to Glasgow are from England, Edinburgh, Stirling and the Highlands.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Flight</strong> - There are two major airports that are close to the city, and those are Glasgow International Airport and Glasgow Prestwick International Airport. The Glasgow International Airport is the closest one to the city centre and lies about 13 kms away. It is serviced by all the major airlines and is the city&#39;s principal airport.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Rail</strong> - Glasgow has two major railway stations. The trains from southern part of Scotland and long distant trains from England arrive at the Central Station also known as the Glasgow Central while the shuttle trains from Northern part of Scotland arrive at Queen Street Station.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Waterways</strong> - If anyone is travelling from Ireland, there are a number of convenient ports that are close to Glasgow. The nearest ferry ports are Troon and Cairnryan for several daily ferries.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - SPT is a local agency that operates a few specialist bus services and the subway. The hub of Glasgow is very much pedestrian friendly and it will be the best if it can be explored on foot. The Subways are another option for transportation and it runs from the city centre through to the West End then runs southwards of Clyde and then turns back to the city. Buses in Glasgow go everywhere and it is the cheapest option among all.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - THE HANOI BIKE SHOP, LOCATED AT 8 RUTHVEN LN. - (FAMOUS FOR BEEF NOODLE &nbsp;SOUP)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - BREAD MEATS BREAD, LOCATED AT 104 ST VINCENT ST. - (FAMOUS FOR BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - THE GRILL ON THE CORNER, LOCATED AT 21-25 BOTHWELL ST. - (FAMOUS FOR OREO MILKSHAKE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - TACO MAZAMA, LOCATED AT 263 BYRES ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR PORK TACOS MADE FROM PORK, &nbsp;FENNEL SEEDS, &nbsp;PAPRIKA, CUMIN SEEDS, ONION, GARLIC, &nbsp;BLACK BEANS, GREEN CHILLI, LETTUCES, CORIANDER, AVACODO, APPLE, TOMATO, SOY SAUCE AND SERVED WITH CHILLY SAUCE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - BABU BOMBAY STREET KITCHEN, LOCATED AT 186 W REGENT ST - (FAMOUS FOR SEV PURI)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - GLAD CAFE, LOCATED AT 1006A POLLOKSHAWS ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR CHILLI AND PUY LENTIL SALAD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - THE HYNDLAND FOX, LOCATED AT 43 CLARENCE DR, HYNDLAND - (FAMOUS FOR EGGS BENEDICT IS A BREAKFAST DISH MADE FROM EGGS, MUFFIN, BACON, HOLLANDAISE SAUCE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - CAFE GANDOLFI, LOCATED AT 64 ALBION ST. - (FAMOUS FOR BRIOCHE FRENCH TOAST)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>9 - SARAMAGO CAFE, LOCATED AT 350 SAUCHIEHALL ST. - (FAMOUS FOR HAGGIS IS A DISH MADE FROM SHEEP&#39;S HEART, LIVER AND LUNGS, AND STOMACH (OR SAUSAGE CASING), ONION, OATMEAL, SUET, SPICES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>10 - OLD SALTY&#39;S, LOCATED AT 337 BYRES ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR MACARONI PIE AND CHIPS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>11 - KEMBER &amp; JONES, LOCATED AT 134 BYRES ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR ROAST BEEF, BEETROOT AND HORSERADISH SALAD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(802, 19, 94, 1842, 'Wales', 'United Kingdom', 'CARDIFF', 'cardiff-175316_640.jpg', 'cardiff-175316_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Located in the southeast corner of Wales, Cardiff became the country&rsquo;s capital in 1955 and launched a number of projects to improve the ancient port city shortly thereafter. The 74200 seat Millennium sports stadium and the futuristic Wales Millennium Centre for the performing arts have now joined Cardiff Castle as the city&rsquo;s star attractions. The 11th century castle gives visitors a great introduction to Welsh history and a climb to the top of the keep offers stunning views of the city and surrounding countryside. Cardiff is the capital city of Wales located in the beautiful United Kingdom and doubles up as the national commercial centre for the continent. As a home to most sporting institutes and national cultural organisations, Cardiff is known for its magnanimous range of attractions and world class entertainment services, including quality shopping avenues. A walk around the town gives a sense of an old world charm that seemingly blends with the modern aura of a new city, where innovative architectural wonders of the new age meet the gothic symbolism of the Middle Ages. It&#39;s a place where the historical buildings takes on a journey filled with exciting facts and lucid historical tales and where the famous Cardiff Bay stands one of the most successful regeneration projects in the United Kingdom. Ancient historical sights and sounds dot the city&rsquo;s landscape, much as the roars of sporting excitement fill the air around all year round. The ambience in the city is that of a romantic one making it one of the best holiday destinations for couples, solo travellers and families alike.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Cardiff is a compact city easily explored on foot from accommodations in its pedestrian city centre. Top notch hotels and B&amp;B&rsquo;s are only a short walk from the major attractions and popular shops. The Welsh countryside along with its quaint country hotels is easily accessible from Cardiff&#39;s centrally located main train station. A gleaming city townhouse hotel, bed and breakfast, bunkhouse or hostel or out in the wilds, where a swathe of green hillside and a curve of golden sand wrap around your own holiday cottage, caravan or campsite.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Cardiff Airport is twelve miles away from the city with direct domestic and international flights to 800 destinations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- The M-4 motorway from London, the M-5 and M-6 from the Midlands, the M-5 and M-4 from South West England and M-4 from West Wales are for those who wish to drive into the city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Right adjacent to the Cardiff Central Station is the Cardiff bus station, which is the centre&rsquo;s hub for coaches and buses coming from other cities into the city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Cardiff is linked by rail directly across all major cities in the UK- Southampton, Bristol, London, and Manchester to name a few. It takes around two and a half hours to reach Cardiff from London.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around </strong>- Cardiff Central Bus Station is the entry and exit point for local buses. There are taxi ranks across Cardiff to choose from and use for transportation needs. Local trains runs east to west and north to south in Cardiff and to major cities across the UK as well thanks to urbanised rail network. Most famous trekking trails are local walks in south east Wales.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - BILL&#39;S CARDIFF CENTRAL RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT 27-39, WYNDHAM ARCADE, MILL LN. - (FAMOUS FOR CHEESE CAKE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - VALENTINO&#39;S, LOCATED AT 5 WINDSOR PLACE - (FAMOUS FOR PASTA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - PURPLE POPPADOM, LOCATED AT 185A COWBRIDGE ROAD E. - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN TIKKA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - CAFE CASTAN, LOCATED AT 5 CATHEDRAL ROAD, LLANDAFF FIELDS, PONTCANNA - (FAMOUS FOR LAMB CAWL IS A DISH MADE FROM LAMB, ONION, POTATO, PARSLEY, PARSNIP AND LEEK)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - MADAME FROMAGE, LOCATED AT 21 CASTLE ARCADE - (FAMOUS FOR WELSH RAREBIT IS A DISH MADE FROM &nbsp;BUCK RABBIT, BLUSHING BUNNY WITH A SAVOURY SAUCE OF MELTED CHEESE AND OTHER INGREDIENTS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - PENYLAN PANTRY, LOCATED AT 72 KIMBERLEY ROAD - {FAMOUS FOR BARA BRITH IS A SWEET BREAD MADE FROM YEAST, MIXED FRUIT (SUCH AS RAISINS, CURRANTS AND CANDIED PEEL)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - LONGHOUSE, LOCATED AT THE TUMBLE, ST NICHOLAS - (FAMOUS FOR LAMB WITH POTATOES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - PORRO LLANDAFF, LOCATED AT 22 HIGH ST. - (FAMOUS FOR BRAISED LEEKS IS A DISH MADE FROM CHICKEN, BUTTER, DRIED THYME)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>9 - SEASONS CAFE BAR, LOCATED AT CASTLE ARCADE, 47-49 CASTLE ST. - (FAMOUS FOR WELSH OGGIE IS A DISH MADE FROM PLAIN FLOUR, BUTTER, EGG OR MILK FILLING WITH ONION, LEEKS, PEPPER, LAMB, POTATO AND MINT SAUCE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>10 - GARLANDS, LOCATED AT &nbsp;4 DUKE ST. - (FAMOUS FOR GLAMORGAN IS A SAUSAGE MADE FROM CHEESE, LEEKS AND BREADCRUMBS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>11 - HOGWURST, LOCATED AT 56 NORTH ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR HOT DOG)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n12 - CALABRISELLA, LOCATED AT 154 COWBRIDGE ROAD E. - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>13 - FRESH, LOCATED AT 32 ROYAL ARCADE - (FAMOUS FOR PEANUT BUTTER, CHOCOLATE CAKE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>14 - FISH AT 85, LOCATED AT 85 PONTCANNA ST - (FAMOUS FOR SEAFOOD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>15 - THE NEW YORK DELI, LOCATED AT 20 HIGH STREET ARCADE - (FAMOUS FOR HOAGIE IS A TYPE OF SANDWICH FILLED WITH A VARIETY OF MEATS, CHEESES, VEGETABLES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>16 - GOT BEEF, LOCATED AT 83 WHITCHURCH ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;BURGER)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n17 - DOROTHY&#39;S FISH BAR, LOCATED AT 39-40 CAROLINE ST. - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;CHICKEN CURRY AND CHIPS)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(803, 19, 94, 1841, 'Northern Ireland', 'United Kingdom', 'BELFAST', 'belfast-953301_640.jpg', 'belfast-953301_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Northern Ireland&#39;s capital is as rich in culture as it is in sweeping scenery and rolling greenery. Belfast is a city steeped in history that is must visit for historians and adventurers alike. Belfast is fast becoming an international hub of creativity and the arts, but it still borrows heavily from its glorious Celtic past. The capital city of Northern Island, Belfast has a long and proud history that means that there is wealth of activities for visitors to enjoy here. To learn all about this history and culture one can head to the Cathedral Quarter where they can wander around to heart&rsquo;s content or simply stroll along the cobblestone streets that line this city as taking in the atmosphere. Not be missed is a trip to a local pub to sample the famous black beer Guinness that really put Ireland on the map. The historic Cathedral Quarter surrounding the ornate St. Anne&#39;s Cathedral in the heart of the city plays host to festivals and events the whole year through. The winding streets are enlivened by performers, while the citadel is one of Belfast&#39;s oldest and most beautiful. The legendary Golden Mile which stretches all the way from the University to the beautifully baroque Belfast City Hall is where the famous Irish party spirit is most present. A cultural meeting point between Britain and Ireland Belfast exhibits an air of determined optimism boasting a growing number of new hotels, bars, restaurants, shops and clubs as well as visitor friendly city centre that has recently been pedestrianized.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Belfast&#39;s tourist friendly and conveniently pedestrian city centre is filled with hotels for a range of budgets. From here one can easily explore most tourist sites on foot or by bicycle. For an authentic Belfast experience consider booking a room at a B&amp;B, hostel or guest house. Alternatively, international brand names and boutique one offs offer top notch amenities. The city centre also houses nightclubs and pubs, where tourists can enjoy an ice cold pint and mingle with the locals.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\n<strong>By Air</strong> - George Best Belfast city airport is just two miles from Belfast&#39;s city centre with magnificent views of the city of Belfast on approach and departure. Belfast International Airport is further from Belfast than city airport lying closer to the towns of Templepatrick and Antrim but offers significantly more international destinations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Services to Dublin is offered by the Enteprise, a modern, comfortable, but relatively slow train jointly operated by Northern Ireland Railways and Iarnrod Eireann Journeys between Dublin and Belfast take two hours and twenty minutes and there are up to eight trains a day, offering two classes of service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Ulsterbus operate the intercity bus network in Northern Ireland, linking most major towns and cities. Services are well used and, in most cases, reasonably priced. The most frequent service is to Londonderry.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Belfast is the focus of the road network in Northern Ireland, and as such is very well connected to the road network in Northern Ireland. While there are only three motorways in Northern Ireland via M-1, M-2 and M-22, the rest of the country is very well provided for with high quality trunk roads.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water</strong> - Frequent sailings across the Irish Sea connect Belfast to mainland Great Britain. An alternative sailing route from London and southern Britain is available via Holyhead and Dublin.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - The centre of Belfast is small enough to be explored by foot. Translink operate Belfast&#39;s urban bus network, called Metro. Buses run along colour coded high frequency routes that radiate from the city centre. Belfast is now famous for its Black Taxi tours of the city which are highly recommended and can be arranged by most hostels, hotels and at the tourist office.</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - DOORSTEPS, LOCATED AT &nbsp;455 LISBURN ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR SANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - ZIZZI, LOCATED AT VICTORIA SQUARE SHOPPING CENTRE - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - KATHMANDU KITCHEN, LOCATED AT 9 BOTANIC AVE. - (FAMOUS FOR ONION AND CHICKEN PAKORA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - FLAME - (LOCATED AT 46 HOWARD ST. - (FAMOUS FOR TANDOORI CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - HOWARD STREET, LOCATED AT 56 HOWARD ST. - (FAMOUS FOR SOUP)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - DEANES, LOCATED AT 36-40 HOWARD ST. - (FAMOUS FOR FISH AND CHIPS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - MADE IN BELFAST, LOCATED AT TALBOT ST. - (FAMOUS FOR BEEF BURGERS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - THE GINGER BISTRO, LOCATED AT &nbsp;6-8 HOPE ST. - (FAMOUS FOR THAI COCONUT CHICKEN CURRY WITH GREENS AND BOILED RICE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>9 - RHUBARB FRESH FOOD CAFE, LOCATED AT 2 LITTLE VICTORIA ST. - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>10 - BIG AL&#39;S BBQ, LOCATED AT 137 STRANMILLIS ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR BURGERS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(804, 19, 94, 1840, 'West Yorkshire', 'United Kingdom', 'LEEDS', 'leeds-1506352_640.jpg', 'leeds-1506352_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Leeds is situated within Yorkshire in England. Considered to be one of the gems of the north, it has an array of Victorian buildings and modern architecture, providing the perfect contrast that most travellers don&rsquo;t get the chance to see in one place. Attracting millions of tourists and students every year it&rsquo;s not shocking that many people find themselves wanting to travel to Leeds while they&rsquo;re in the north of England. Leeds is a traveller&rsquo;s delight and is considered to be one of the best tourism destinations in the United Kingdom. Also dubbed as the city of festivals Leeds is a vibrant city with different festivals celebrated all year round. There are so many activities in the city that are sure to enthral any traveller to this tourism hotspot. Shopping, sightseeing, food festivals, musical events, carnivals these are just a few among the myriad things the city has to offer. A visit to one of the famous pubs is a must while in the city. Drop in at the historic White locks Pub or the Adelphi Pub to get a glimpse of English pub culture. Depending on interest one can visit the city at a time when a particular event is held or just randomly pick a date and visit. In either case, travellers will always find something fun and interesting to do in the city. Once upon a time Leeds was drab industrial city. Now it&rsquo;s a cultural and commercial hub where one will find free festivals, a lively waterfront and pedestrianised streets lined with shops, bars that bring in the partygoers, restaurants selling dishes from around the world and Leeds Festival, sister festival to the legendary Reading Festival. Leeds city centre is a shopper&rsquo;s paradise, offering visitors everything from sparkling shopping centres to big brand retailers and independent boutiques, many being housed in renovated Edwardian and Victorian era buildings.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">From luxury hotels to good old fashioned B&amp;B&rsquo;s, there&rsquo;s accommodation in Leeds to match all tastes and budgets. There are hotels in Leeds to suit every taste and budget, ensuring a relaxing break and most importantly, a good night&rsquo;s sleep. Leeds is home to a number of huge names when it comes to hotels. Whether its business or pleasure it&rsquo;s sure to find a perfect hotel in Leeds. Stay in a family run B&amp;B and enjoy a warm welcome to Leeds. A home cooked meal in a comfortable environment can make all the difference to the trip.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Leeds is mainly served by the Leeds Bradford Airport also known as Yeadon Airport. The airport is the highest airport in England located at an altitude of 681 ft above sea level. The Airport is the 16th busiest airport in the UK.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The city of Leeds is also well connected by rail network with the major cities and regional towns of the country. Leeds Railway Station is located on New Station Street. Cross Country and Virgin Trains are the two important rail services that connect the city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Leeds is well connected by bus. Travellers can take the National Express or Megabus coaches to reach the city. Road transport is very efficient in the country and a bus trip to the city is quite enjoyable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - The city is connected to other parts of the country from all directions through the M-1 highway, M-62 highway and the A-1 highway.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - Buses are the main mode of public transportation in Leeds. There are plenty of cab services in the city such as City Cabs, Streamline Telecabs and others. Metro service in Leeds is run and operated by Metro brand, which is the West Yorkshire Combined Authority responsible for public transport. Local train in Leeds is operated by the Northern Rail. Leeds offers a lot of walking, hiking and trekking options.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - HUMPIT HUMMUS &amp; PITA BAR, LOCATED AT &nbsp;CALL LN - (FAMOUS FOR FALAFEL IS A DEEP-FRIED BALL MADE FROM FAVA BEANS OR CHICKPEAS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - GROVE CAFE, LOCATED AT &nbsp;133-135 CARDIGAN ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;PIZZA , ROASTED TOFU, MUSHROOMS AND VEGAN CHEESE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - FILMORE &amp; UNION, LOCATED AT &nbsp;6 &nbsp;HARROGATE ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR SOUP AND SALAD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - MRS ATHA&#39;S, LOCATED AT &nbsp;CENTRAL ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR CAKES, COFFEE, &nbsp;WHITE CHOCOLATE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - THE GREEDY PIG, LOCATED AT &nbsp;58 NORTH ST - (FAMOUS FOR FRIED CHICKEN, PANCAKES AND CHICKEN WINGS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - HEPWORTH&#39;S DELI AND KITCHEN, LOCATED AT &nbsp;21, THORNTONS ARCADE, LANDS LN - (&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;FAMOUS FOR SANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(805, 19, 94, 1839, 'Merseyside', 'United Kingdom', 'LIVERPOOL', 'port-999625_640.jpg', 'port-999625_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Famed for its wonderful culture, winning football teams, The Beatles and a buzzing nightlife, Liverpool is one of the major cities of UK situated in Merseyside in England. It lies within the boundaries of Lancashire. It was awarded as the European Capital of Culture in 2009 and is home to some of the major attractions in Europe. The seaport of Liverpool is located in the North western part of England and it is at a distance of 336 kms from London. This town has a reputation of wit and the people have an obsession over football and music. Along with that it also has an impressive cultural heritage and it is home to more museums than any other city apart from London. The galleries here are among the best in the country and are a major shopping destination as well. It is one of the major premier ports in England thanks to its location. There have been two decades of complete urban regeneration and now the city has a sparkling new waterfront with latest shops and restaurants. It is a blend of the old heritage and the urban culture. The nightlife scene in Liverpool is also really famous. Liverpool is home to one of Britain&rsquo;s biggest industrial heritages. Like much of the North of England, Liverpool has its roots in the industrial revolution, when it became a major port. This made it a hub for diversity and culture as people from all over the world travelled into England via Liverpool. Liverpool is considered to be a capital of culture in both England and Europe, with numerous art galleries, museums and a vibrant nightlife.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Liverpool has wide range of tourist accommodations and most of them are located towards the centre of the city. But the hotels in city centre are pretty expensive and cater to majorly business travellers. If looking for some budget places to stay, it is to stay outside the city centre. Mount Pleasant is a good area to scout for budget accommodation. Liverpool is packed with all kinds of hotels, including international chains, posh hostels, independent boutique hotels, family run B&amp;B&rsquo;s and historical country mansions. To take advantage of the city&#39;s explosive culinary and cultural scene, consider staying in Liverpool&#39;s historical central district.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - There are daily bus services from Liverpool ONE bus station. London is located four to five hours away by bus and there are nearly half a dozen services per day. There are also hourly services to Manchester.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - The city of Liverpool is well connected to the UK motorway networks and one can take the M-62, M-56 or M-58 to reach the destination. There are private taxis and cabs available to the nearby locations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Liverpool John Lennon Airport is the main airport in the city and it has almost 160 flights that arrive daily from within UK and Europe. The major airlines that serve here are Easyjet and Ryanair.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Travelling to Liverpool by train is one of the easiest and the best ways of commutation. It takes only 2 hours and 13 minutes to reach Liverpool from Central London. It also has frequent rail services from Leeds, Newcastle, Nottingham, Manchester and Birmingham.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water </strong>- There are regular scheduled ferries that operate from Douglas and Belfast to Liverpool. These are not much popular, yet are a great way to reach the city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - Getting around is most easily accessible by the local bus services. There are also frequent rail services to connect to the outskirts of the city. The city is not that large that one cannot walk around, but there are still black hackney cabs in case feeling lazy. Tourists can also hire the private taxis.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - BACCHUS GREEK TAVERNA, LOCATED AT &nbsp;14 WATERLOO ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR GREEK SALAD IS A SALAD MADE FROM TOMATOES, CUCUMBERS, ONIONS, FETA CHEESE, OLIVES (USUALLY KALAMATA OLIVES), SALT, OREGANO AND OLIVE OIL)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - FAZENDA, LOCATED AT &nbsp;EXCHANGE FLAGS, HORTON HOUSE, EXCHANGE ST E - {FAMOUS FOR MUSHROOM AND PEPPERCORN GNOCCHI(DUMPLINGS MADE FROM POTATOES (OR SEMOLINA OR WHEAT FLOUR, EGGS, CHEESE)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - LOBSTER POT, LOCATED AT &nbsp;20-22 WHITECHAPEL - (FAMOUS FOR FISH AND CHIPS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - FREE STATE KITCHEN, LOCATED AT &nbsp;1 MARYLAND ST - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;ONION BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - MARAY, LOCATED AT &nbsp;91 BOLD ST - {FAMOUS FOR HUMMUS( IS A SPREAD MADE FROM CHICKPEAS,OR OTHER BEANS BLEND WITH &nbsp;OLIVE OIL, LEMON JUICE, SALT, GARLIC, TAHINI) AND GREEN CHILLI FRIES}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - RAGGAS, LOCATED AT &nbsp; SMITHDOWN ROAD - (FAMOUS FOR JERK CHICKEN)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n7 - HOST, LOCATED AT &nbsp;31 HOPE ST. - (FAMOUS FOR DUCK AND WATERMEL ON SALAD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - AMALIA, LOCATED AT &nbsp; 2 CAMPBELL SQUARE - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>9 - THE EGG, LOCATED AT &nbsp;TOP FLOOR, 16-18 NEWINGTON - (FAMOUS FOR SOUP AND CHEESE ON TOAST)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>10 - BAKCHICH, LOCATED AT 54 BOLD ST. - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN SHAWARMA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>11 - 81 RENSHAW, LOCATED IN &nbsp;LIVERPOOL - (FAMOUS FOR CHEESE CAKE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>12 - BACARO, LOCATED AT &nbsp;47 CASTLE ST. &nbsp;- (FAMOUS FOR LOBSTER MAC AND CHEESE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>13 - ALMOST FAMOUS, LOCATED AT &nbsp;11-13 PARR ST. - (FAMOUS FOR BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>14 - SOUL CAFE, LOCATED AT &nbsp;114 BOLD ST - (FAMOUS FOR MILKSHAKE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>15 - LIVERPOOL - {FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;WET NELLY IS A DESERT MADE FROM WHITE BREAD, BUTTER, BROWN SUGAR, MILK, MIXED FRUIT, EGGS ; BUBBLE AND SQUEAK IS A DISH MADE FROM POTATOES, CABBAGE, BRUSSELS SPROUTS, VEGETABLES ; TOAD IN THE HOLE IS A DISH MADE FROM SAUSAGES, YORKSHIRE PUDDING, BATTER, ONION GRAVY}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(806, 14, 95, 1838, 'St. Petersburg', 'Russia', 'ST. PETERSBURG', 'beauty-2105726_640.jpg', 'beauty-2105726_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Often regarded as Russia&rsquo;s most European and forward looking city, St. Petersburg makes for a wonderful travel destination, especially for history and culture lovers. More than 2000 libraries, 220 museums and 80 theatres make up the city&rsquo;s well established cultural landscape, while edgy art galleries, bohemian cafes, boisterous underground clubs and cool hostels with minimalist Scandinavian interiors show off St. Petersburg&rsquo;s innovative side. The UNESCO listed historic centre with its fascinating network of canals and eye catching Baroque and Neoclassical architectural styles is certainly a must for everyone visiting the former capital of Russia. And so are the city&rsquo;s greatest museums the fabulous Hermitage and the Russian Museum, or the bustling Nevsky Prospekt St. Petersburg&rsquo;s main avenue and its premier destination for shopping, dining and nightlife. The city&rsquo;s elaborately decorated churches, the world famous Mariinsky Theatre, the Peter and Paul Fortress and the Vasilyevsky Island are well worth a visit as well. The best time to visit St. Petersburg is during summer, when the city is experiencing its famous White Nights a time of glorious midnight sun, beautiful traditions and numerous night time festivals. St. Petersburg is a popular destination with travellers looking for a city break in Russia and its coastal location makes it a great base if travelling around the Baltic for holidays. The country&rsquo;s cultural epicentre St. Petersburg is known for its distinctive European flavour that blends with traditional Russian style.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">St. Petersburg is big and as such has many good neighbourhoods where one can stay. Staying in or near the city centre are the most convenient options, since most of the attractions are nearby and to just walk around from place to place. The comfort hotels are cheaper option here. The Nevsky Prospekt offers good access to many places too and is a vibrant area to stay in. The Petrogradskaya is an amazing island district of the city, where one will also find accommodations ranging from the super luxurious to the perfectly reasonable. It has several popular restaurants and is also well connected to the rest of the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - St. Petersburg is served by 3 intercity bus terminals. It is connected to many domestic cities like Novgorod, Vologda, Vyborg, Smolensk and Pskov and also to quite a few international destinations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Pulkovo Airport is St. Petersburg&#39;s international airport. The city is fairly well connected to other destinations across Europe, Asia and the Middle East. All domestic flights also operate from the Pulkovo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - St. Petersburg&#39;s rail connectivity is very good. Rail routes connect St. Petersburg to the rest of the country, from one end to the other. It is connected to Finland as well, with a route operating from Helsinki.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water</strong> - St. Petersburg is connected via waterways to the Scandinavian region and a few other European countries. There are also river cruises which connect the city to Moscow, via the Volga, Onega and Ladoga lakes and the Neva.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - Public transport in St. Petersburg is very convenient. The system consists of buses, trams, metros and even fixed route cabs. The city is extensively connected by these various means of public transport. The metro system is beautifully decorated, has 5 lines and connects 67 stations.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - KARTOFEL&rsquo;S GRIBAMI OR POTATOES WITH MUSHROOMS, LOCATED AT &nbsp;GOROKHOVAYA ST, 12 - {FAMOUS FOR KAPSALON IS A FAST FOOD MADE FROM FRENCH FRIES, MEAT ( SHAWARMA), CHEESE, SALAD VEGETABLES}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - BURO BYRGERY, LOCATED AT &nbsp;ZHUKOVSKOGO 29 - {FAMOUS FOR BURGER, TOMATO SOUP WITH PESTO, BASIL AND CROUTONS(BAKED BREAD)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - PITA&#39;S, LOCATED AT &nbsp;GOROKHOVAYA ST., 32 - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;FALAFEL &nbsp;IS AFRIED DOUGH FOOD &nbsp;MADE FROM FAVA BEANS OR CHICKPEAS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - OBEDBUFET, LOCATED AT СС &nbsp;NEVSKY AVENUE, 114 - {FAMOUS FOR SOUPS, PIZZA AND KEFIR IS A DRINK MADE FROM MILK, KEFIR GRAINS (BACTERIA, SALT, YEASTS, PROTEINS, LIPIDS, SUGAR)}<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n5 - ST. PETERSBURG - {FAMOUS FOR GOLUBTSI IS A FOOD MADE FROM MINCED MEAT WITH RICE, WRAPP IN CABBAGE LEAVES AND STEWED IN TOMATO SAUCE WITH PRUNES, GREENS, PEPPER OTHER SPICES (THYME, CORIANDER, BASIL) ; OLADYI IS A TYPE OF PANCAKE MADE FROM BUCKWHEAT FLOUR, EGGS, MILK, SALT, SUGAR WITH YEAST AND SERVED WITH SMETANA (SOUR CREAM), SWEET TOPPINGS WITH VARENYE, JAM, HONEY ; PLOV IS A FOOD MADE FROM RICE, SPICES, MEAT OR FISH, VEGETABLES AND DRIED FRUITS ; VINAIGRETTE IS A SALAD MADE FROM BEETROOTS, CARROTS, POTATOES, PEAS, PICKLED CUCUMBERS}</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(807, 14, 95, 1837, 'Moscow', 'Russia', 'MOSCOW', 'russia-2123697_640.jpg', 'russia-2123697_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Moscow is Russia&#39;s capital and its cultural, economic and political heart. It is the largest and the most populated city in Russia and also a city of huge global influence. It is the country&#39;s biggest tourist destination, home to some of the most historic architectural works in the country. Moscow is a city with a very rich past. It served as Russia&#39;s capital for a long time and after the Bolshevik Revolution became the capital of Russia again. It has one of the best collections of architectural structures in the world. The Kremlin which serves as the residence of the Russian President today is an emphatic complex of palaces, cathedrals and walls. The iconic St. Basil&#39;s Cathedral is one of the most unique cathedrals anywhere in the world. Moscow has huge number of museums as well displaying artworks from throughout the history of Russia. There is even a display of priceless jewellery and state regalia in the Kremlin Armoury. Apart from that, Moscow is home to many splendid gardens and parks that find their origins in the imperial era. These parks today have been restored and beautified and are a favourite hangout spot for locals who are looking for some time away from their busy lives. Gorky Park, Tsaritsyno and the Alexander Garden are an example of the remarkable gardens in the city. The city&#39;s nightlife is world famous and so is its shopping symbolised by the GUM on the Red Square. Several musical concerts and cultural events take place often in the city and the city is also home to Russia&#39;s national theatre, the Bolshoi Theatre. Moscow provides with a huge variety of activities and is sure to keep tourists occupied throughout the trip. When done with it all, take a hike up Sparrow Hills and absorb a beautiful panorama of the city.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The capital of Russia and a huge metropolis, Moscow offers a plethora of different types of accommodations. Many renowned hotel chains are represented in the city and some of its hotels rank among the world&#39;s most luxurious and expensive. Those travelling on a more modest budget can choose among the boutique or Soviet era hotels. There are also numerous hostels and short term rental apartments throughout the city. The Arbat region is also located conveniently and has many good options. It is advised to stay close to the Red Square for the best access to attractions and activities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Moscow is one of the most important cities in the world and is served by three main international airports namely Sheremetyevo International Airport, Domodedovo Airport and the Vnukovo International Airport. It can be reached from nearly all international airports all over the world and all the major airlines of the world operate flights to Moscow.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Moscow is extensively connected via rail to all of Russia, East Asia and also Europe. It has a total of nine railways stations serving various routes. Going towards Europe, Moscow is connected to Paris, Berlin, Warsaw, Vienna, Prague, Helsinki, Belarus and Budapest.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Moscow is decently connected with nearby towns and cities such as Suzdal within the Moscow oblast. International bus routes to Europe are also available to locations like Berlin, Budapest, Warsaw, Prague and a few other cities.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Getting into Moscow is not a difficult task as all Federal Highways heading into Moscow from other countries are marked by &#39;M&#39;. Driving into Russia however, requires paperwork which should be taken care of prior to the trip. Cities in the Moscow oblast are very conveniently connected as well via highways.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - Public transportation in Moscow is rather convenient. The Moscow Metro is actually one of the most popular metros in the entire world. Buses run throughout the city and each street has at least one bus operating on it and connecting to the nearest metro station. Moscow also operates a tram service throughout the city. Taxis and Multinational cab services also operate throughout the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - MOSCOW - {FAMOUS FOR LEPYOSHKA IS A TYPE OF FLAT BREAD FILLED WITH GROUND MEAT, CHEESE, OR POTATO ; BLINI IS A TYPE OF PANCAKE MADE FROM WHEAT OR &nbsp;BUCKWHEAT FLOUR AND SERVED WITH SOUR CREAM, QUARK, BUTTER, CAVIAR ; SBITEN IS A DRINK BASED ON HONEY MIXED WITH WATER, SPICES, AND JAM ; BEEF STROGANOFF IS A DISH MADE FROM BEEF, SMETANA (SOUR CREAM) ; PIROZHKI IS A FRIED FOOD MADE FROM YEAST DOUGH FILLED WITH MEAT (TYPICALLY BEEF), VEGETABLE (MASHED POTATOES, MUSHROOMS, ONION EGG AND CABBAGE) ; APPLE SHARLOTKA IS A DISH MADE FROM APPLES, LEMON JUICE, SUGAR, FLOUR, CINNAMON, NUTMEG, EGG AND ALMOND ; KASHA IS A TYPE OF PORRIDGE MADE FROM CEREAL (BUCKWHEAT, WHEAT, BARLEY, OATS, MILLET OR RYE) ; KNISH IS A SNACK MADE FROM MASHED POTATOES, DOUGH, GROUND MEAT, SAUERKRAUT, ONIONS, KASHA, CHEESE}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - COTTAGE ON POKROVKA, LOCATED AT &nbsp;POKROVSKY BLVD, 18, стр. 1 - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;OLIVIER SALAD AND BORSCHT)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - CAFE PUSHKIN, LOCATED AT TVERSKOY BOULEVARD, 26А - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;PELMENI IS A DUMPLING MADE FROM FLOUR, EGGS FILLED WITH MINCED MEAT OF (PORK, LAMB, BEEF), FISH OR MUSHROOM)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - MARI VANNA, LOCATED AT SPIRIDONYEVSKIY PER., 10A - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;SYRNIKI IS A TYPE OF PANCAKE MADE FROM QUARK CHEESE, FLOUR, EGGS, SUGAR, &nbsp;RAISINS, VANILLA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - CRAFTED BAR, LOCATED AT SOKOLNICHESKOGO KRUGA DRIVE, 5 - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN SOUP AND BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - POINT COFFEE FOOD, LOCATED AT &nbsp;SADOVNICHESKAYA NAB., 75 - (FAMOUS FOR COFFEE)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', '');
