(808, 14, 95, 1836, 'Sochi', 'Russia', 'SOCHI', 'sochi-2202950_640.jpg', 'sochi-2202950_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Called the summer capital of Russia, the busy resort town of Sochi is best known as the host of the 2014 Winter Olympics. Sochi boasts plenty of beachside destinations great for everything from water sports to more leisurely pursuits. Sochi Beach and Dagomys Beach are two of the more popular beaches in this region. Khosta Beach and Adler Beach are some of the other coastal destinations in this region. Perhaps the most popular ski resorts around in this region are Krasnaya Polyana Ski Resort and also Estosadok Ski Resort. These two places offer some excellent entertainment. Sochi is an idyllic seaside retreat that attracts hundreds of people to it each year, including celebrities and renowned politicians. The city is also called the Black Sea Pearl. Sochi is a popular spot among tourists, attracting a whopping total of more than 4 million visitors each year. It also has something on offer for everyone parks for nature lovers, museums and other sites for history lovers and beautiful beaches. Long the favourite haunt of Russia&#39;s political elite, Sochi advertises itself as the hub of the Russian Riviera, offering warm summers and mild winters. Venture farther away from the coastline to discover city&#39;s sprawling parks tranquil places that offer shady canopies of old magnolia and cypress trees. Sochi also hosts the Russian Formula 1 Grand prix and will be a host city for the 2018 Fifa World Cup. Despite winter snow, Sochi offers a subtropical climate and great beaches, making it a key part of the Russian Riviera. The resort city makes a great summer getaway for Russians. Strolling along the pedestrian only sea embankment is a pleasant experience.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">While travelling can be exciting, it can be exhausting so it&rsquo;s important to choose the perfect accommodations to rest. Sochi offers a variety of wonderful hotels. There are from 5 stars to mid-range options and budget hotels available here at Sochi. From subtropical seaside luxury hotels to chic chalets in the Alps, there are lot of places to stay in Sochi.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Sochi International Airport sees dozens of carriers coming in, both domestic and international. Yakutia, Turkish Airlines and S-7 are the most common carriers.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Board a train from St. Petersburg or Moscow and reach Sochi in just over a day. There is also a double Decker train for this route.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Sochi&#39;s bus terminal is very close to the city&#39;s train terminal. Buses get in from Ukraine, Moldova, Abkhazia as well as Nalchik, Astrakhan and other nearby cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Driving down from Europe to Sochi is quite possible and can be achieved within a day&rsquo;s time, in case of good drivers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - Sochi is dotted with minibuses, commonly called Marshrutka. This is the most popular form of transport in Sochi. Trolley buses are also available and are popular choices for long distance trips.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - AMSHENSKY DVOR RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT &nbsp;KRASNOFLOTSKAYA UL., 15-A, KRASNODARSKIY KRAY - (FAMOUS FOR SOLYANKA IS A TYPE OF SOUP MADE FROM MEAT, FISH, OR MUSHROOMS, PICKLED CUCUMBERS WITH BRINE, OFTEN CABBAGE, SMETANA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - STARYY BAZAR, LOCATED AT &nbsp;UL. NESEBRSKAYA, 4&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; - (FAMOUS FOR KHACHAPURI IS A TYPE OF PIE MADE FROM CHEESE, EGGS, BREAD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - BELYE NOCHI, LOCATED AT &nbsp;MORSKOY PER., 7, KRASNODARSKIY KRAY - (FAMOUS FOR KHINKALI IS A TYPE OF DUMPLING FILLED WITH SPICED MEAT OF (BEEF, PORK, LAMB), HERBS, ONIONS, GARLIC, CHEESE, POTATO, OR MUSHROOM)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - DEL MAR, LOCATED AT &nbsp;PRIMORSKAYA UL., 11, SOCHI, KRASNODARSKIY KRAY - (FAMOUS FOR CHEESE BALL)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - PUZATA HATA, LOCATED AT &nbsp;NAVAGINSKAYA UL., 9/1, KRASNODARSKIY KRAY - (FAMOUS FOR BORSCH IS A TYPE OF SOUP MADE FROM &nbsp;BEETROOT)</strong></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(809, 14, 95, 1835, 'Novosibirsk', 'Russia', 'NOVOSIBIRSK', 'city-1768160_640.jpg', 'city-1768160_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Situated in Siberia&#39;s southwestern portion, Novosibirsk developed into a major urban centre in the last decade of the 19th century, when it became a convenient pit stop for railway travellers making the epic Trans-Siberian journey. Stretching along the banks of the Ob River, the vast city serves as Siberia&#39;s unofficial capital a major industrial and transportation centre boosted by its rich coal and mineral deposits. Filled with museums and monuments Novosibirsk also boasts energetic nightlife and a diverse restaurant scene known for offering classic specialties and outstanding wines from around the world. Despite its size Novosibirsk features a manageable city centre famous for containing Russia&#39;s largest opera house. Novosibirsk in Novosibirsk Oblast is located approximately 1191 kms north of Guilin and about 2816 kms east of the national capital Moscow. The Novosibirsk War Memorial is a quiet place of contemplation where locals and visitors can come to honour those who have lost their lives in past wars. In this culture loving city, be sure to investigate some of the remarkable exhibit spaces such as the Novosibirsk State Museum where inquiring minds can learn and be challenged. Enjoy the atmosphere, ask the friendly staff about the guided tours, pick up a souvenir at the gift shop or just admire the treasures of the past. Bring the kids to a trip to Novosibirsk Zoo, the primary zoological park in Novosibirsk. The residents here are sure to delight the entire family so leave at least a few hours to explore this educational zoological experience.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">An urban oasis in vast expanses of Siberia, Novosibirsk offers all types of accommodations one would expect of a large, well developed city. As the third largest city in Russia, it&#39;s the home of a great selection of hotels, ranging from full luxury to more economic options. Many of these are centrally located, and if arriving by train tourists can find a number of lodgings near the city&#39;s main station. Those looking for more economical accommodation can choose from a variety of charming and welcoming hostels. Renting fully furnished apartments is a popular option here.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The city is served by the international airport Tolmachevo located 17 kms from the centre of Novosibirsk. The airport offers regular passenger flights to major cities of Russia, countries of the former Soviet Union and the United Arab Emirates.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Novosibirsk railway station is really one of the best in Russia. It was renovated not long ago and is very comfortable and clean. The Trans-Siberian Railway passes through the city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - The main bus station is located in the south of the city on Krasny Prospekt and buses depart to all local destinations including the direction of Altai Mountains.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water</strong> - Novosibirsk is also an important port on the Ob River and there are regular ferries and cruise services to and from Novosibirsk to major ports of Russia and the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - As in any Russian city in Novosibirsk there are public buses, trolleybuses, minibuses marshrutkas and even a metro. However, the most popular transport in Novosibirsk is taxis.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - BEERMAN, LOCATED AT 7, KAMENSKAYA STREET - (FAMOUS FOR PELMENI IS A TYPE OF DUMPLING MADE FROM FLOUR, WATER,EGGS FILLED WITH MEAT OF &nbsp;(PORK, LAMB, BEEF), FISH OR MUSHROOMS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - VEGGIE PIT, LOCATED AT MICHURINA 8 K2 - (FAMOUS FOR BURGERS, KEBABS, FALAFEL AND PIZZA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - BOTTVA, LOCATED AT DOBROLYUBOVA 2A (AT BC RIVERPORT) - (FAMOUS FOR TORTILLA, SALADS, SOUP, COUSCOUS AND FRUIT JUICES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - LA MAISON, LOCATED AT SOVETSKAYA ULITSA, 25 - (FAMOUS FOR CAKES AND PASTRIES)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(810, 14, 95, 1834, 'Kazan', 'Russia', 'KAZAN', 'kazan-801910_640.jpg', 'kazan-801910_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kazan, a city deriving its name from the Tartar word for cooking pot, is a true melting pot of cultures. Known as the Istanbul of Russia, the East meets West atmosphere here derives from Kazan&rsquo;s true diversity of culture and religion which is reflected in its architecture, history and cuisine. Over 1000 years of history have left their mark on the city, making for a truly spectacular skyline. Kazan is sometimes referred to as the Istanbul of the Volga because it is a city where European and Asian cultures meet. The capital of Tatarstan is a lovely city where church tower and minarets fill the skyline. Also known as the third capital of Russia, after Moscow and St. Petersburg, Kazan residents enjoy one of the highest standards of living in Russia. Sights to see include the remains of the Kazan Kremlin that was destroyed by Ivan the Terrible, the Kul Sharif Mosque named after a man killed defending Kazan from Ivan and Bauman Street a pedestrian shopping street. Kazan offers a selection of interesting spots to visit. Kazan Kremlin and the Kul Sharif Mosque are the best bets. Republic of Tatarstan is a firm fixture on the tourist trail which means getting around is a breeze. Make sure to leave enough time to explore the incredible range of things to see and do the region offers. Watch some of Russian&#39;s favourites when the FC Rubin Kazan takes on their rivals at the iconic Central Stadium in Kazan. To endear with the locals be sure to wear maroon, the colours of the FC Rubin Kazan.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kazan boasts a selection of accommodations to match every taste and budget. While it may lack the extravagance of some of Moscow&#39;s high end hotels, it still offers a good selection of both modern and historical luxury lodging. Most of the city&#39;s best known hotels sit relatively close to the centre. Venture just beyond the centre to find several smaller boutique hotels, bed and breakfasts and hostels as well as numerous fully furnished apartments available for short term rental.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Kazan International Airport is 30 kms to the southeast of the city centre. Aeroflot, S7, Transaero and UT-Air fly between Kazan and Moscow and Rossiya Airlines also flies to Kazan from Saint Petersburg.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Kazan&#39;s train station is located close to the city centre with several hotels, restaurants and the Kremlin within walking distance of the train station. Kazan is easy to reach by train, as it is a major station stop for several west east trains.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Bus is maybe not the fastest but the cheapest option. Tourists should also be prepared for traffic jams and the bus full of people, so the trip could be a bit exhausting.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water</strong> - Kazan has a riverboat terminal on the Volga River and can be reached by river cruise as well. River cruises down the Volga operate during the summer months. Dozens of boats operated by different companies run from Moscow to Astrakhan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - Kazan&#39;s city centre is small enough to walk between most places of interest. Buses, trams, trolleybuses and taxi vans are the cheapest and most efficient modes of transport but there is also a small metro and taxis are fairly cheap.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - KAZAN - {FAMOUS FOR KYSTYBY IS A DISH MADE FROM FLOUR, MILK, BUTTER, SOUR CREAM, EGG, SALT, POTATOES, ONION ; ECHPOCHMAK IS A DISH MADE FROM FLOUR, YEAST, SOUR CREAM, EGG, SUGAR FILLED WITH CHICKEN, POTATOES, ONIONS, BUTTER, SALT AND PEPPER ; KAZYLYK IS A SAUSAGE MADE FROM HORSE MEAT, SALT, PEPPER ; PIROG SMETANA IS A PIE MADE FROM APPLES, SUGAR, EGGS, BUTTER AND FLOUR, SMETANA [SOURED CREAM, OR MELTED BUTTER ; PEREMECHIKI IS A TYPE OF CAKE MADE FROM ONIONS, EGG, SALT, MILK, WHEAT FLOUR, SOUR CREAM, BUTTER, YEAST AND SUGAR ; KAKLAGAN KAZ IS AN AIR-DRIED GOOSE ARE RUBBED WITH SALT AND WRAPPED IN WAX PAPER ; SHASHLIK IS A DISH MADE FROM MEAT OF LAMB, &nbsp;MARINADE, ONIONS ; CHAK-CHAK &nbsp;IS A SWEET MADE FROM EGGS, SUGAR, FLOUR, HONEY AND VODKA OR BRANDY}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - DOM CHAYA, LOCATED AT &nbsp;BAUMAN ST, 64 - (FAMOUS FOR GUBADIYA IS A SWEET DIUSH MADE FROM STUFFED MEAT FILLED WITH A MIXTURE OF RICE, NUTS AND RAISINS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - BILYAR RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT BUTLEROVA, 31 - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;UKHA IS A SOUP MADE FROM FISH (STURGEON, SALMON, COD), ROOT VEGETABLES, LEEKS AND POTATOES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - STOLOVAYA, LOCATED AT &nbsp;SEROVA, 9 - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;CREPE IS A TYPE OF PANCAKE MADE FROM WHEAT FLOUR OR BUCKWHEAT FLOUR, MILK AND EGGS)</strong></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(811, 14, 95, 1833, 'Vladivostok', 'Russia', 'VLADIVOSTOK', 'bridge-430446_640.jpg', 'bridge-430446_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Mountains and bays surround Vladivostok, making it a stunning beautiful city in Russia&rsquo;s east. The last stop on the Trans-Siberian Railway, Vladivostok is the country&rsquo;s largest port on the Pacific Ocean it is just a hop, skip and a jump away from North Korea and China. The city offers many cultural attractions from theatres to museums to concerts, actor Yul Brynner was born here in 1920. Travellers may want to stroll through some of the city&rsquo;s lovely parks including Minny Gorodok which was once a military base. The city&rsquo;s main square is Admiralsky Skver, with a museum devoted to a submarine nearby. Often compared to San Francisco and Naples, the sprawling eastern city of Vladivostok serves as the largest Russian port on the Pacific Ocean. Established in 1860 as a military post, the city grew into a major centre of commerce and transportation. Closed to foreign travellers from 1958 to 1992, Vladivostok now draws big tourist crowds with its hilly streets, centenarian buildings, and busy bay area, named the Golden Horn after a similarly shaped harbour in Istanbul. Farther away from the water the city turns into a mass of gray housing blocks remnants of the glum Soviet days. Vladivostok is in Primorsky Krai which is known for its captivating beaches, coastal plains and forests.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">One of the most popular destinations of the Russian Far East, Vladivostok offers its visitors plenty of options for a place to stay. Tourists will find many centrally located hotels, as well as those in residential areas and because of the city&#39;s bay location, sea view rooms are not an uncommon feature. Several high end hotels cater to well heeled travellers while those with more modest budgets will also find plenty of options including smaller hotels, bed and breakfasts and hostels.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Vladivostok International Airport is 40 kms northeast of Vladivostok, near Artyom. It is the largest airport in the Russian Far East and serves over 1.5 million passengers per year. Flights to and from Vladivostok are to other Russian cities or cities in Korea, China or Japan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The facade of Vladivostok&rsquo;s train station is the city&rsquo;s most recognizable landmark. The overnight Okean train runs between Khabarovsk and Vladivostok. The Rossiya train makes the trip all the way to Moscow.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - The Vladivostok&rsquo;s bus station is in the Second River region. Buses operate to and from most suburban locations and nearby towns. International routes link Vladivostok to cities in north eastern China such as Harbin, Mudanjiang and Suifenhe.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water</strong> - The ferry port in Vladivostok is right next to the train station. Business In tour Service is the official booking agent for ferries operated by The Far Eastern Shipping Company between Vladivostok and the Fushiki port in Takaoka, Japan. It is also possible to travel to and from anywhere in the world by booking a berth on a cargo boat.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - Vladivostok has a wide range of transportation, from streetcars to funicular railway, trams and trolleybuses. By far the most common is the bus and marshrutka shared taxis. There are a number of taxi companies and hailing one is easy. The city centre is only a short walk from the train station and most of the sights can be reached easily on foot. Ferry boats run between Vladivostok Sea Passenger Terminal and nearby islands.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - CAFE ALI BABA, LOCATED AT POGRANICHNAYA 6, ACROSS FROM THE STADIUM - (FAMOUS FOR BABA GHANOUSH IS A &nbsp;DISH MADE FROM EGGPLANT AND OLIVE OIL)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - CAFE 3T, LOCATED AT ALEUTSKAYA PROSPEKT 43 - (FAMOUS FOR SANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - MAGIC BELL, LOCATED AT SVETLANSKAYA, NEXT TO DOM OFFISEROV FLOTA - (FAMOUS FOR CHIMICHANGA IS A DEEP-FRIED BURRITO MADE FROM TORTILLAS, RICE, CHEESE, MACHACA, JALAPE&ntilde;O, CARNE ADOBADA OR &nbsp;CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - MAGIC BURGER, LOCATED AT SVETLANSKAYA 44 - (FAMOUS FOR BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - MAURO GIANVANNI, LOCATED AT FOKINO 1B. CLOSE TO THE STADIUM AND THE WATERFRONT - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - CAFE IGUANA, LOCATED AT SVETLANSKAYA 23 - (FAMOUS FOR COFFEE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - CAFE EXPRESS, LOCATED AT OKEANSKY PROSPECT 10-12 - (FAMOUS FOR SOUPS, SALADS, AND MEAT DISHES)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(812, 14, 95, 1832, 'IRKUTSK', 'Russia', 'IRKUTSK', 'irkutsk-911832_640.jpg', 'irkutsk-911832_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">The de facto capital of Eastern Siberia, Irkutsk is by far the most popular stop on the Trans Siberian Railway between Moscow and the east. With Lake Baikal only 45 kms away, the city is the best base to explore the lake&rsquo;s western shoreline. Travellers who visit historic Irkutsk may be pleasantly surprised by what they find. Decorated wooden houses stand beside standard Soviet bloc apartments, plus wide boulevards with not too much traffic for a city of more than 500000 souls. Irkutsk was the site of many bloody clashes between Russian factions in various revolutions. It also served as a place of exile for intellectuals, artists and others which may be why the city has five universities. Several churches including Ascension Church and geology and history museums call Irkutsk home. Irkutsk gained fame as the cultural centre of Decembrist exiles. In the early 1800s, Russian artists, officers and nobles who participated in the Decembrist revolt against Tsar Nicholas-I were exiled to Siberia. Enjoy the city&#39;s proximity to many beloved natural sites, including Lake Baikal. Tour this alluring destination and take in views of its ornate architecture, wooden houses and wide streets which earned it the nickname of the Paris of Siberia. There are some cool ways for thrill seekers to experience the great outdoors in and around Irkutsk. Ice skating and hiking are just two popular ways active visitors can get their thrills. For those who love to rug up and head outdoors in winter, this area may just be an excellent place to go.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">With steadily increasing popularity among tourists, Irkutsk offers a good selection of places to stay. The centre of the city has the highest concentration of luxury and boutique hotels, but one can also find quite a few in other neighbourhoods. Numerous bed and breakfasts and plenty of hostels offer a good alternative to hotels. Likewise, renting a fully furnished apartment is another popular option.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - International Airport Irkutsk is 5 kms east of the city centre. Direct flights operate to and from Moscow, Saint Petersburg, Ulan Ude, Novosibirsk, Vladivostok, Yakutsk and several other Russian cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The train station in Irkutsk is the major hub on the Trans-Siberian railway mainly used to access Baikal Lake. It&rsquo;s located 15 minutes from the centre of the city and there are many buses and taxis departing from it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - There is also the main bus terminal in the centre of the city where tourists can catch a bus to Olkhon Island or Listvyanka. Buses to those both destinations depart around 4 times a day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - As usual there are buses, trolleybuses, and trams in the city. They cover most of the city centre. The best thing to do is to ask the driver for the destination before getting inside. The historical centres of Irkutsk are relatively compact and walk able.</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - IRKUTSK - {FAMOUS FOR TSUIVAN IS A STEW MADE FROM FLOUR, NOODLES, WATER, OIL, MEAT WITHOUT BONES, VEGETABLES, ONION, GARLIC CLOVES, SALT AND PEPPER ; SALAMATA IS A DISH MADE FROM FLOUR, CREAM, MILK, SUGAR, EGG AND BUTTER ; RASSOLNIK IS A &nbsp;SOUP MADE FROM PICKLED CUCUMBERS, PEARL BARLEY, AND PORK OR BEEF KIDNEYS ; BAKED OMUL IN A SPECIAL SAUCE}<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - POPCAFE, LOCATED AT UL. LITVINOVA, 17, IRKUTSK, IRKUTSKAYA OBLAST - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA AND LASAGNE IS A TYPE OF PASTA MADE FROM DURUM WHEAT)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n3 - FISHERMAN HOUSE, LOCATED AT PARTIZANSKAYA ULITSA, 47 - (FAMOUS FOR FISH DISHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - BUZA, LOCATED AT UL. CHERNYSHEVSKOGO, 8 - (FAMOUS FOR PASTRIES, NOODLES WITH CHICKEN AND MUSHROOM SOUP)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - NEAPOL, LOCATED AT UL. ALEKSANDRA NEVSKOGO, 21 - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(813, 19, 96, 1831, 'Berlin', 'Germany', 'BERLIN', 'brandenburg-gate-2447149_640.jpg', 'brandenburg-gate-2447149_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Cool, sophisticated, cutting edge and packed to the very tip of its iconic TV tower with culture, history and character, Berlin is one of Europe&rsquo;s undisputed bucket list capitals. At its very heart famed Museum Island oozes with everything from classical antiquities plucked from Babylon to Troy, while the darker tales of the 20th century can be uncovered at spots like Checkpoint Charlie, the crumbling remnants of the Berlin Wall and the striking Jewish Memorial by Peter Eisenman. Then there&rsquo;s boho centre of Friedrichshain Kreuzberg, awash with cafes and cool jazz joints, ad hoc craft studios and artsy galleries, all of which is neatly balanced with the straight laced Reichstag, the Brandenburg Gate and summertime picnics in the Tiergarten. Berlin is all things exuberant and vibrant. It is extravagant, yet affordable, cosmopolitan and forward yet steeped in rich history. The morbid days of Cold War and a city divided by the Wall are long forgotten and the reunified capital beats fast as the heart of Germany. Berlin was the stage to some events that not only shaped world history but were revolutionary in it headquartered by the Nazis, bombed by the Allied forces, partitioned and reunited, only recently. Far from being anguished by its turbulent 20th century history, the capital has resurrected itself as one of Europe&#39;s most stirring cities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The majority of Berlin&#39;s better lodging choices are located in the Mitte and Schoneberg neighbourhoods of Berlin. These neighbourhoods are where tourists will find many of the luxury options and in contrast to other European metropolitan areas, Berlin offers run the gamut from high end luxury options to almost shockingly cheap, yet still very liveable hostels. For a peaceful residential area, try Charlottenburg-Wilmersdorf where the streets are lined with boutiques and quiet coffee shops.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The city is served by two airports. The Tegel International Airport is the main airport for international carriers and is a hub for domestic flights. The Schonefeld airport is the base for charter flights, many low cost airlines and most of the traffic from Eastern Europe.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Berlin&#39;s Hauptbahnhof receives the Euro City and Inter Regio trains from all major European cities, most of them being direct trains. The Hauptbahnhof is centrally located and well connected to all means of public transport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Travelling to Berlin by bus has become easy, affordable and popular. The coaches are all air conditioned and some even offer free on board Wi-Fi. Each of the operators has their respective websites which one can refer to for schedules and reservations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Berlin is connected by A-2 from the west, the A-11 from the North, the A-9 from the south and the A-12 from the east. All these roads have outlets at the Berliner Ring, the outer ring road of the city.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water</strong> - Berlin does not have a seaport. Nearest seaport is Rostock Warnemunde, which is between two and a half and three hours away by train. The tickets are still sold by many cruise ship operators as Berlin, so don&rsquo;t be surprised.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - The U-Bahn (underground) and the S-Bahn (light rail) are the most convenient and efficient ways of travel. Metro trams ply only in the east districts. Taxis and Ubers are available on the go and are fairly inexpensive. Cycling is a nice way to explore Berlin as there are several bike lanes and rental places.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - CURRY UND CHILI, LOCATED AT OSLOER STR., 13359 - (FAMOUS FOR CURRY WURST IS A SNACK DISH MADE FROM PORK SAUSAGE, CURRY KETCHUP)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - MUSTAFA&#39;S GEMUSE KEBAP, LOCATED AT MEHRINGDAMM 32, 10961 - (FAMOUS FOR DONER KEBAB IS A SNACK MADE FROM LAMB, BEEF OR CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - CURRY 36, LOCATED AT MEHRINGDAMM 36, 10961 - (FAMOUS FOR BOCKWURST IS A SAUSAGE &nbsp;MADE FROM GROUND VEAL AND PORK, FLAVORED WITH SALT, WHITE PEPPER AND PAPRIKA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - ALAIN SNACK, LOCATED AT SCHONHAUSER ALLEE 116A, 10437 - (FAMOUS FOR KETWURST IS A TYPE OF HOTDOG MADE FROM BREAD ROLL, BOCKWURST AND KETCHUP)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - ZUR LETZTEN INSTANZ, LOCATED AT WAISENSTRABE 14-16, 1017 - {FAMOUS FOR EISBEIN IS A DISH MADE FROM HAM HOCK AND SERVED WITH WITH MASHED POTATOES OR SAUERKRAUT( CUT CABBAGE)}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - ORCHARDT, LOCATED AT FRANZOSISCHE STRABE 47, 10117 - (FAMOUS FOR SCHNITZEL A LA HOLSTEIN IS A DISH MADE FROM FLOUR, BREAD CRUMBS, MILK, EGGS, VEAL CUTLETS, &nbsp;BLACK PEPPER,UNSALTED BUTTER, FILETS(BONELESS MEAT OR FISH), PARSLEY, AND LEMON JUICE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - BACKEREI SIEBERT, LOCATED AT SCHONFLIEBER STR. 12, 10439, (FAMOUS FOR BERLINER IS A TYPE OF PASTRY&nbsp;MADE FROM YEAST DOUGH, JAM, POWDERED SUGAR)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - THE BIRD, LOCATED AT AM FALKPL. 5, 10437 - (FAMOUS FOR BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>9 - BEAKERS, LOCATED AT DUNCKERSTRABE 69, 10437 - {FAMOUS FOR FRIED EGGS WITH FETTA(CHEESE), PANCAKES, SANDWICHES}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>10 - MARIA BONITA, LOCATED AT DANZIGER STRBE33, 10435, (FAMOUS FOR QUESADILLA IS A FOOD MADE FROM TORTILLAS, CHEESE, MEAT, SALSA, MUSHROOM, REFRIED BEANS, AVOCADO OR OTHER VEGETABLES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>11 - DADA FALAFEL, LOCATED AT LINIENSTRABE 132, 10115 - (FAMOUS FOR FALAFEL IS A IS A DEEP-FRIED BALL MADE FROM FAVA BEANS OR CHICKPEAS AND HUMMUS &nbsp;IS A LEVANTINE DIP OR SPREAD MADE FROM CHICKPEAS OR OTHER BEANS, BLENDED WITH TAHINI, OLIVE OIL, LEMON JUICE, SALT AND GARLIC)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>12 - JONES, LOCATED AT GOLTZSTRABE 3, 10781 - (FAMOUS FOR ICECREAM)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>13 - BERLIN - {FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;KARTOFFELPUFFER IS A TYPE OF PANCAKE MADE FROM POTATOES, FLOUR, CHICKEN EGG, AND COOKING OIL, FLAVORED WITH GRATED GARLIC OR ONION, TOPPED WITH SOUR CREAM OR COTTAGE CHEESE ; APPLESTRUDEL IS A TYPE OF PASTRY MADE FROM FLOUR, OIL OR BUTTER, APPLES ; KUNEFE IS A DESERT MADE FROM SUGAR, CHEESE, PISTACHIO, ROSE WATER AND KAYMAK(IS A CREAM)}</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(814, 19, 96, 1830, 'Bavaria', 'GERMANY', 'MUNICH', 'maximilianeum-2472685_640.jpg', 'maximilianeum-2472685_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Best known as the origin of the world famous Oktoberfest, Munich is a major international hub for research, technology and medicine. The capital of the state of Bavaria, Munich is Germany&rsquo;s most prosperous city, boasting research universities and global companies like BMW and state of the art science museums such as the Deutsches Museum. However, Munich is not all business. This vibrant city offers one of Germany&rsquo;s best culture scenes, presenting several sophisticated opera houses and theatres like the National Theatre. The city centre is an attractive blend of classic and modern architecture, teeming in historic churches, medieval walls and royal palaces as well as bustling shopping centres, art galleries and nightlife venues. Munich also offers its share of lush green spaces, which include the English Garden, one of the world&rsquo;s largest public parks. Munich is home to sports teams consisting of basketball, ice hockey and a championship football club. Munich&rsquo;s Oktoberfest began in 1810 with a royal wedding celebration. Today, this famous beer festival draws millions of visitors every year to take part in the revelry that involves several gigantic beer tents, delicious Bavarian food, fun competitions and millions of litres of beer. No matter what time of year tourist&rsquo;s visit, they can experience Munich&rsquo;s beer gardens and beautiful beer halls. Munich today is the technology capital that values quality of life over and above all other aspects. Nevertheless the Bavarian city retains a medieval charm. It&#39;s a city that guilelessly blends modernity and tradition. The chic and fashionable co exists with Leather pants, rustic beer halls and wursts.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Munich has an assortment of hotels, B&amp;Bs and hostels to cater to all budgets. However availability tends to be an issue since this city apart from being a tourist favourite all year round plays host to major trade fairs during January-March and of course the Oktoberfest, in the last week of September. Hence making advance reservations will not only reduce hassle but also be easy on wallet. Hotels in Munich run the gamut from budget hostels to classy five star and the best choice for short term visitors no matter what type of budget one is on is to stay downtown in the Altstadt downtown city centre where the palaces, churches and other city landmarks are located.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Flughafen Franz-Josef Strauss or the Munich International Airport is the main connection for incoming and outgoing international and domestic flights from all continents with over 80 carriers operating to and from here.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Munich has a well connected train network, to other cities in Bavaria, as well as some distant cities in Germany as well as Europe. All trains arrive and depart from Central Station. Destinations include Vienna, Prague and Paris as well amidst the other German cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- Zentraler Omnibusbahnhof (ZOB) receives coaches both domestic and international. Eurolines connects Munich to the Romantic Road, further on to other German cities. A special coach also travels to Prague departing from the ZOB.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Munich is accessible via roads A-8, A-9 and A-95 from nearby cities of Nuremberg, Salzburg and Stuttgart etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - Munich has an efficient public transport system facilitated by buses, trams, the U-Bahn and the S-Bahn. The U-Bahn and S-Bahn stations are located at all primary places and run almost 24 hours a day. Night buses and trams operate only in the city centre though. Taxis ply by the metre with additional charges for luggage.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - MUNICH - {FAMOUS FOR KNODEL IS A TYPE OF DUMPLING MADE FROM &nbsp;POTATOES OR BREAD OR FLOUR ; BRATWURST IS A TYPE OF SAUSAGE MADE FROM &nbsp;MEAT (VEAL, PORK OR BEEF) ; &nbsp;APPLE STRUDEL IS A TTPE OF PASTRY MADE FROM FLOUR, OIL OR BUTTER, APPLES ; &nbsp;GERMKNODEL IS A TYPE OF SWEET BREAD MADE FROM YEAST DOUGH, SUGAR, &nbsp;BUTTER, POPPY SEEDS, PLUM JAM ; FISCHBROTCHEN IS A TYPE OF SANDWICH MADE FROM BREAD, FISH, ONIONS, REMOULADE AND PICKLES, CREAMY HORSERADISH SAUCE, KETCHUP OR COCKTAIL SAUCE ; OBATZDA IS A TYPE OF CHEESE MADE FROM CHEESE (USUALLY CAMEMBERT), BUTTER, PAPRIKA POWDER, SALT, PEPPER, BEER}<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - JA MAI, LOCATED AT &nbsp;PESTALOZZISTRABE 9 - {FAMOUS FOR PHO IS A NOODLE SOUP MADE FROM RICE NOODLES AND BEEF OR CHICKEN}</strong></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - SCHNELLE LIEBE, LOCATED AT THALKIRCHNER STR. 12 - (FAMOUS FOR BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - BERGWOLF, LOCATED AT FRAUNHOFERSTRABE 17 - (FAMOUS FOR CURRYW&uuml;RST &nbsp;IS A TYPE OF &nbsp;BRATWURST MADE FROM PORK SAUSAGE, CURRY KETCHUP)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - PUNKTO, LOCATED AT M&uuml;LLERSTRABE 48 - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - PARDI, LOCATED AT VOLKARTSTRABE 24 - (FAMOUS FOR FRIED CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - MUNCHNER SUPPENKUCHE, LOCATED AT AM VIKTUALIENMARKT ABT. 3 STAND 5/28/29 - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;CARROT-COCONUT-GINGER SOUP)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - CAFE FRISCHHUT, LOCATED AT PR&auml;LAT-ZISTL-STRABE 8 - (FAMOUS FOR YOUTIAO IS A FRIED FOOD MADE FROM FLOUR, VEGETABLE OIL, YEAST, SUGAR, SALT, AND WATER)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n9 - RESTAURANT DALLMAYR, LOCATED AT DIENERSTRA&szlig;E 14 - (FAMOUS FOR COFFEE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>10 - BRENNER, LOCATED AT MAXIMILIANSTRABE 15 - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;PASTA AND &nbsp;GRILLED VEGETABLE SALAD WITH GREEN ASPARAGUS, ZUCCHINI, CORN, ONIONS, AVOCADO, TOMATOES WITH GRILLED CHICKEN)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(820, 19, 96, 1899, 'Saxony', 'GERMANY', 'DRESDEN', 'dresden-2360843_640.jpg', 'dresden-2360843_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Situated in the Far East corner of Germany, Dresden boasts a reputation for being one of the country&rsquo;s most striking cities. Before it was severely damaged in World War II, the city was known as the Jewel Box because of its lavish collection of stunning art and architecture. After many years, most of the tourist attractions in Dresden haven been fully restored, including world famous landmarks like the magnificent Zwinger Palace and the Semper Opera House. Dresden, which is the capital of the Free State of Saxony, is situated along the pretty Elbe River. This remarkable city is truly a cultural and architectural wonderland. After decades of post-war reconstruction, the city has restored its classic baroque skyline while also adding newly renovated museums, edgy architecture and innovative restaurants. Music, food, porcelain, the world&#39;s most beautiful dairy and the Blue Wonder, the Saxon capital is packed with a punch. Dresden is an intermingling of the past, present and future an eclectic mix of art, culture, history, tradition as well as technology. The Frauenkirche and the Zwinger stand on the banks of Elbe in perfect harmony with Volkswagen&#39;s Die Glaserne Manufaktur. For over centuries, Dresden has been renowned for its music. The city is host to a plethora of international festivals, theatre and dance productions and the very popular Semper Opera Ball, all year round. Synonymous to the music scene here is the Jazz form, the Dixieland Festival being Europe&#39;s oldest and biggest Jazz festivals, reverberates through the city during May. Dresden is a treat all year round.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Hotels in Dresden are up to international standards and often far outshines its West German counterparts. In Dresden it is a usual affair to have a major international hotel in a 1000 year old house or restored mansion. Smaller and family run hotels are more charming local options and often include a good restaurant. Accommodation for all budgets ranging from hostels to luxury hotels are scattered all over the city. For an area that stays active both day and night, consider lodging in Aussere Neustadt, located northeast of the Old City.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Airport Dresden International, 9 kms north of the city centre has flights arriving from continents across the world. Alternatively the Leipzig Halle Airport is also used by several tourists. All major airlines operate to and fro both these airports.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Dresden is an important railway junction within the ICE and EC/IC networks of the German Railways. Direct international connections are also there to and from Aarhus, Budapest, Prague, Vienna, Zurich and others.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Dresden has three entry points by road. The A-4 approaches the city from the West and the A-13 from the North, while the A-17 connects the city with Prague. Moreover, the federal highways B-6, B-97, B-170, B-172 and B-173 connect Dresden to the transport network.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Direct coaches connect other major cities in Germany to Dresden. Bayerische Strasse and Station Dresden-Neustadt are the halts for these buses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - Dresden has an efficient and well connected tram and bus network, operated by Dresdner Verkehrsbetriebe. The Elbe ferries are convenient ways to cross the river, to get to places within the boundaries of the city. Another popular way of exploring the city is by hiring bicycles. The Dresden City Card and the Dresden Region Card can be purchased for prepaid travel within the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>1 - KASTENMEIERS, LOCATED AT TZSCHIRNERPL. 3-5, 01067 - (FAMOUS FOR PANCAKES)</strong></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>2 - BRUHLSCHER GARTEN, LOCATED AT BRUHLSCHER GARTEN 4 - (FAMOUS FOR GRANOLA IS A SNACK FOOD CONSISTING OF ROLLED OATS, NUTS, HONEY OR &nbsp;BROWN SUGAR, AND PUFFED RICE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>3 - CAROLASCHLOSSCHEN, LOCATED AT QUERALLEE 7 - (FAMOUS FOR COFFEE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>4 - LADEN CAFE AHA, LOCATED AT &nbsp;KREUZSTRA&szlig;E 7, 01067 - (FAMOUS FOR SHAKES AND VEGAN CURRY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>5 - KUPPELRESTAURANT IN DER YENIDZE, LOCATED AT WEI&szlig;ERITZSTRA&szlig;E 3, 01067 - (FAMOUS FOR POTATO SOUP WITH GRILLED SAUSAGES AND CREUTONS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>6 - LADENCAFE AHA, LOCATED AT KREUZSTRABE 7 - (FAMOUS FOR POTATO SOUP)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>7 - STULLENBURO, LOCATED AT GORLITZER STR. 37 - (FAMOUS FOR SANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>8 - ROOTS, LOCATED AT HAUPTSTRABE 35 - (FAMOUS FOR VEGGIE BURGERS AND SWEET POTATO FRIES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>9 -KASTENMEIERS ,LOCATED AT TZSCHIRNERPL. 3-5, 01067 - (FAMOUS FOR SEAFOOD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><strong>10 - CURRY AND CO, LOCATED AT LOUISENSTRABE 62 - (FAMOUS FOR GERMAN SAUSAGES WITH INNOVATIVE SAUCES LIKE JALAPE&ntilde;O AND PEANUT)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', ''),
(821, 19, 96, 1900, 'Hesse', 'GERMANY', 'FRANKFURT', 'frankfurt-1909660_640.jpg', 'frankfurt-1909660_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Frankfurt is the 5th largest city in Germany and also the largest city in the state of Hesse. Situated on the Main River, Frankfurt is Europe&#39;s financial capital and a global hub for tourism, commerce, education and culture. It has the busiest airport in Germany and one of the world&#39;s largest stock exchanges. Though it seems like the city is all work and no play, at its heart it remains to be charming and old fashioned. Frankfurt has beautiful parks, riverside paths, gardens, delightful neighbourhoods and quaint taverns serving apple wine with yummy regional food. After Berlin, Frankfurt has the most museums. It also has a vibrant nightlife with lots of entertainment spots. The city has the most diverse culture with the country&#39;s largest foreign population. Whether on business or a vacation, here are many things to do at Frankfurt like visiting the gothic Saint Bartholomeus Cathedral. Take a stroll through the halls of one of the city&#39;s numerous galleries, watch a flick at the German Film Museum or make way to the top of the Main Tower for breathtaking views of the city. The town isn&rsquo;t only famous for its modern towering buildings, after visiting the Old Town tourists will get an idea of how Frankfurt looked like before it became the financial capital of the European Union. Although much of the city was destroyed by Allied bombing during World War-II, many of the buildings were saved in the Altstadt.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Frankfurt offers many hotels for all types of travellers. The most convenient ones, but pricier, are located downtown. The central location allows enjoying the evening happenings all within a safe, walk able area. Hauptwache, Konstablerwache, and the Main River enclose the heart of the city, an area of activity with a range lodging options. The old section of the Sachsenhausen area is also an epicentre of activity with a range of accommodations; it also offers a vibrant nightlife.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Frankfurt Airport is among the busiest in Europe, 3rd in passenger traffic after London Heathrow and Paris Charles de Gaulle Airport and the 9th busiest airport in the world. All major airlines and all airline alliances fly frequently to Frankfurt and connect it to every continent and major city in the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- Frankfurt Hauptbahnhof is one of the biggest and busiest train stations in Europe and has a beautiful architecture, so it&#39;s definitely worth a visit. Frankfurt has connections to most German cities and most neighbouring countries via Intercity and high speed Intercity Express trains.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- Frankfurt is serviced by various trans-European bus lines like Eurolines. The main terminus is the central station. If on a tight budget, this can be a good way to reach Frankfurt.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around </strong>- There are a number of inter-city bus routes, particularly in the north. Taxis are found in most parts of the city. They have bright taxi plates on the roof of the car. The U-Bahn and S-Bahn are the most convenient modes of transport within the city. Frankfurt is a great city to discover on foot. There are numerous walking tours and self guided city walks as well.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - FRANKFURT - {FAMOUS FOR FRANKFURTER RINDSWURST &nbsp;IS A SAUSAGE MADE FROM BEEF ; BETHMANNCHEN IS A TYPE OF PASTRY MADE FROM MARZIPAN, ALMONDS, POWDERED SUGAR, ROSEWATER, FLOUR, EGGS ; FRANKFURTER KRANZ IS A TYPE OF CAKE MADE FROM SPONGE CAKE, BUTTERCREAM, RED JAM (STRAWBERRY, BLACKCURRANT OR CHERRY JAM), NUTS, ALMOND &nbsp;AND HAZELNUTS}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - BURGER BABY, LOCATED AT HOHENSTRABE 24 - (FAMOUS FOR BURGERS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - IIMORI PATISSERIE, LOCATED AT BRAUBACHSTRAVBE 24, 60311 - (FAMOUS FOR CUCUMBER SALAD AND SPRING ROLLS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - EBERT&#39;S SUPPENSTUBE, LOCATED AT GROBE BOCKENHEIMER STR. 31, 60313 - (FAMOUS FOR &nbsp;POTATO SOUP WITH SAUSAGE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - ZUM-FEUERRAEDCHEN, LOCATED AT TEXTORSTRA&szlig;E 24, 60594 - (FAMOUS FOR POTATO SOUP)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - ZUM GEMALTEN HAUS, LOCATED AT SCHWEIZER STR. 67, 60594 - (FAMOUS FOR EGGS WITH GREEN SAUCE)</strong></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', '');
