(849, 19, 99, 1919, 'Innsbruck', 'AUSTRIA', 'INNSBRUCK', 'innsbruck-358307_640.jpg', 'innsbruck-358307_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Tucked away in the dramatic landscapes of the Alps, Innsbruck is a true alpine gem and renowned worldwide for its ski resorts and tradition of hosting winter sports competitions. Its long history as the centre of the Tyrol region and modern history as a winter sports haven draw people from all over the globe. Innsbruck, the Capital of the Alps, delights with its unique wealth of wonderful attractions between 574 and 2350 mts above sea level. Alpine urban, sporty, dynamic and cosmopolitan yet charming, strong and traditional Innsbruck is a city with exceptional appeal. Innsbruck offers diverse cultural events, world famous attractions, exciting city tours, great highlights in the centre and surrounding mountains, genuine hospitality, modern lifestyle and sporting flair. Innsbruck also known as the Capital of the Alps has everything a lively, vibrant city needs and yet it is just a ten minute journey into the high mountains which dominate the skyline. Innsbruck, with a name that translates as bridge over the inn, is an all season tourist destination. It is internationally known for its winter sports, having hosted the Winter Olympics in 1964 and 1976. But this Tyrolean city offers more than just great skiing. It offers a good mix of cathedrals such as Hofkirche which houses the tomb of Emperor Maximilian-I, the Schloss Ambras which has a collection of paintings and armour and the Bell Museum a nod to 400 years of bell making. Innsbruck was one of the first places to embrace snowboarding when the sport appeared on the scene in the 1990s and the city maintains this alternative subculture today, with a strong population of skateboarders and snowboarders. Innsbruck is more than just a snowboarding mecca, however the city&rsquo;s opulent Habsburg palaces, medieval city centre and lively nightlife round out the destination&#39;s appeal.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Innsbruck has the perfect accommodation for every different desire, budget and taste. From fully equipped hotels with regal ambience and top class food, via homely bed and breakfasts to hostels and rooms for the smallest purse, everything is possible in Innsbruck whether for a luxury trip or even backpacking. The Alpine gem of Austria, Innsbruck offers a surprising amount of reasonably priced accommodations for its size. Look for hostels and hotels in the medieval centre. Another option is to stay above the city on the Hungerburg Plateau, where one will find Alpine hotels with panoramic views from each room.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Innsbruck Airport is located on the western edge of the city and offers maximum comfort, short transfers and unique flair. Innsbruck Airport also called the Kranebitten Airport is the largest airport that serves the region. The airport has also become a well established venue for events and seminars thanks to its fantastic location and stunning panoramic views.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Though Innsbruck is a small city, it has a well connected network of trains operated by Osterreichische Bundesbahnen, OEBB. The railway station Innsbruck Hauptbahnhof is located in the eastern part of the city. Innsbruck is readily accessible from several cities such as Zurich, Venice, Graz, Bolzano/Bozen, Munich and Vienna.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Innsbruck is easily accessible via buses from other nearby cities. Flixbus operates buses to Innsbruck from several nearby cities. A bus ride from Munich will take around two hours and ten minutes and it will take around five and a half to six hours to reach Innsbruck from Salzburg depending on the type of bus and the time of journey.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Exceptional flexibility and ideal links with Central Europe&rsquo;s main transport routes make driving to Innsbruck a particularly pleasant experience. The journey is easy and stress free thanks to well developed road networks that make for easy access to the city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - Innsbrucker Verkehrsbetriebe is responsible for operating public transport in the city of Innsbruck. A number of buses operate in the city and even connect it to the surrounding areas. Taxi Innsbruck operates taxis for tourists to get around the city. Hiring a car is a convenient option for moving around in Innsbruck. Innsbruck is the perfect place for both taking leisurely walks and engaging in some challenging hikes.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - STIFTSKELLER, LOCATED AT STIFTSGASSE 1-7, 6020 - (FAMOUS FOR ROASTED CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - LUDWIG, LOCATED AT MUSEUMSTRA&szlig;E 3, 6020 - (FAMOUS FOR BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - CAFE KROLL, LOCATED AT HOFGASSE 6, 6020 - (FAMOUS FOR STRUDEL IS A TYPE OF PASTRY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - GOLDENES DACHL, LOCATED AT HOFGASSE 1, 6020 - (FAMOUS FOR SCHLUTZKRAPFEN IS A TYPE OF PASTA MADE FROM BUCKWHEAT FLOUR, WHITE FLOUR, SEMOLINA, EGGS, OLIVE OIL, CHEESE, SPINACH AND MUSHROOMS</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - FLOJOS, LOCATED AT SEILERGASSE 12, 6020 - (FAMOUS FOR NACHOS IS A SNACK COMPOSED OF TORTILLA CHIPS COVERED WITH CHEESE OR CHEESE-BASED SAUCE)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(850, 19, 99, 1920, 'Linz', 'AUSTRIA', 'LINZ', 'linz-853946_640.jpg', 'linz-853946_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Linz is a beautiful and sometimes underrated city located in the northern part of Austria on the River Danube. As the third largest city in Austria, it is actually of major importance and also a great tourist destination with many interesting sights and activities. The great combination of historical buildings, stunning architecture, vast areas of green space and modern innovations mean that Linz has as much to offer as such high ranking Austrian cities as Vienna and Salzburg. Since 2014 Linz has been part of the UNESCO creative cities network and this is apparent with the brilliant array of museums one can visit here. Also known as the European Capital of Culture, Linz is a city that not only preserves its traditions but actively promotes its cultural heritage across borders. While tradition is held high, it is combined with ideas of innovation by engaging in extraordinary projects and constant redefinition of the city&rsquo;s cultural side. Located on the Danube with a rolling green backdrop, Linz is a city equally rich in nature and culture. The Culture Mile along the Danube combines the two. Austria&#39;s third city is home to a host of museums, festivals and churches some as old as the 800s. Though it was the city where Adolf Hitler spent his youth Linz has a history as a city of peace and it works to uphold that reputation. Linz is a symbiosis as a city of industry, culture and nature and an international, contemporary creative city surrounded by stunning natural landscapes. The city&rsquo;s designation as a UNESCO City of Media Arts shows that Linz, together with Lyon, Sapporo, Tel Aviv and Dakar is one of the world&rsquo;s most future orientated locations. In addition to pioneering technology and visionary media arts the city offers a variety of historical and cultural highlights as well as culinary delights.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><br />\r\nThere&#39;s a variety of accommodation providers to choose from for staying in Linz. From luxurious four star hotels to guesthouses and hostels, there&#39;s something for every taste. Many of the accommodations are family run and housed in historical buildings full of charm. If want to stay in Linz&#39;s large well known Altstadt there are many lodging options. Consider locations near the central Hauptplatz or Main Square for convenience. Treat to a spot near the picturesque Danube, which cuts through town.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The Blue Danube Airport is at the gates of the city, just 20 minutes away from the centre. There are direct flights to Linz from Dusseldorf, Frankfurt, London, Salzburg and Vienna.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - The Osterreichische Bundesbahnen offers convenient, low cost connections from the whole of Austria and neighbouring countries. The main station is close to the centre and directly linked to all major transport routes. Since 2011, the new Westbahn rail service covers the Vienna to Salzburg route via Linz in 3 hours</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Water</strong> - Linz is situated on one of Europe&#39;s most important waterways, the Danube, which is linked to the Rhine and the Main. Linz is a popular stopover for cycle tourists on the Danube bicycle path from Passau to Vienna.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Shuttle bus, CK Shuttle and Czechshuttle offers door to door shuttle bus transportation services between Linz and Salzburg, Hallstatt, Vienna and Cesky Krumlov.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Linz is connected with Vienna, Salzburg, and Munich via the A-1 motorway, the Muehlviertel A-7 Autobahn and the south of Austria, Klagenfurt via the A-9 Autobahn. It is also connected to Germany via Passau through motorway A-8.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around </strong>- Linz has a very good public transport service. A lot of the tram and bus lines are available. Public and private car rental services are also available throughout the city.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - LEBERKASPEPI, LOCATED AT RATHAUSGASSE 3, 4020 - (FAMOUS FOR LEBERKASE IS A FOOD CONSISTS OF CORNED BEEF, PORK AND BACON)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n2 - BURGERISTA, LOCATED AT ALTENBERGERSTRABE 6, 4040 - (FAMOUS FOR BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - KONDITOREI JINDRAK, STAMMHAUS AND KUNSTCAFE, LOCATED AT HERRENSTRABE 22, 4020 - (FAMOUS FOR LINZER TORTE IS A TYPE OF CAKE MADE FROM FLOUR, BUTTER, EGG YOLKS, CINNAMON, LEMON JUICE, GROUND NUTS (HAZELNUTS, WALNUTS OR ALMONDS) AND JAM)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - SCHINDLER&lsquo;S HEURIGER, LOCATED AT EISENBAHNGASSE 18, 4020 - (FAMOUS FOR ROASTED PORK)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - BROTSUCHTIG GMBH, LOCATED AT HERRENSTRABE 8, 4020 - (FAMOUS FOR PASTRIES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - RIKSCHA BISTRO, LOCATED AT HOFGASSE 12, 4020 - (FAMOUS FOR SOUP)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - BURGER CHECKER, LOCATED AT FREISTADTER STR. 313, 4040 - (FAMOUS FOR HAMBURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>8 - HORST DEKO AND GENUSS, LOCATED AT MOZARTSTRA&szlig;E 19, 4020 - (FAMOUS FOR CAKE AND COFFEE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>9 - BIG JOE, LOCATED AT GRABEN 28, 4020 - (FAMOUS FOR FALAFEL IS FRIED DOUGH FOOD MADE FROM FAVA BEANS OR CHICKPEAS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>10 - VIETNAM PHO, LOCATED AT FREISTADTER STR. 60, 4040 - (FAMOUS FOR PHO IS A TYPE OF NOODLE SOUP MADE FROM &nbsp;RICE NOODLES AND BEEF OR CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>11 - PIZZERIA BELLA CASA, LOCATED AT AUBRUNNERWEG 1A, 4040 - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(851, 19, 99, 1921, 'Klagenfurt', 'AUSTRIA', 'KLAGENFURT', 'minimundus-375285_640.jpg', 'minimundus-375285_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Klagenfurt is the capital of the state of Carinthia in Austria with a population of around 99000 and is the sixth largest in the country. Due to a more southerly location, Klagenfurt has cold winters but relatively warm summers and is in a prime position on the shores of the popular Lake Worthersee. The city has a myriad of attractions and is a great place to use as a base to explore southern Austria with absolutely jaw dropping landscapes and mountain scenery. Klagenfurt is situated in southern Austria, near the border with Slovenia, and is bounded on the south by the wooded ridge of the Sassnitz range, with the Karawanken rearing up behind. Founded in 1161 as a market town, Klagenfurt is famous for its extremely attractive Old Town quarter with its picturesque lanes, historical buildings and its many arcaded Renaissance courtyards with their trendy boutiques, galleries and cafes. It&#39;s also famous for the old moat and canal added between 1527 and 1558 and which still links Klagenfurt to the Worthersee, the area&#39;s largest lake. Also of interest are the city&#39;s old fortifications, marked by a circuit of streets known as the Ring, which circles the old part of the town and boasts many fine parks and gardens. As host of the Euro 2008 football tournament, Klagenfurt held its own as a host, showing that it was a dynamic city that knew how to party. Perhaps this is due to its Italian influences, which can be felt both in the city&#39;s architecture, with its pleasant courtyards and squares and in its food. Positioned on the shore of a lake, Worthersee, less than an hour from Slovenia and Italy the capital of Carinthia wins visitors over with its Mediterranean feel and its art of living. Klagenfurt, which was first mentioned in 1192, boasts one of Austria&rsquo;s historic town centres and was thrice awarded the prestigious Europa Nostra Diploma for its lovingly restored arcaded Renaissance courtyards, which today accommodate modern boutiques, trendy bars and authentic beer gardens. The Lindwurm, a winged dragon that is the landmark of the city was modelled on a legendary dragon, said to have resided in a swamp here long ago, dominates Neuer Platz.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Klagenfurt offers a range of accommodations. Stay in the Innere Stadt or Inner District, for the most central location to all the city&rsquo;s tourist attractions. If looking for nightlife and a lively atmosphere, check out accommodations near the university. If a central location isn&rsquo;t a priority, try to snag a room on the Worthersee, the large lake near the city. The city hotels are located in the city centre of Klagenfurt, directly at the central Cathedral Square and are an ideal choice for vacation or business trip to Klagenfurt.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Klagenfurt has its own international airport Flughafen Klagenfurt. Scheduled flights operate to Klagenfurt from London, Berlin, Bonn, Munich, Hamburg, Hannover, Dusseldorf &nbsp;and Vienna.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Since Klagenfurt is located at a railway gateway to Italy, Slovenia and Germany, it can be easily reached by any bigger Austrian city. There are hourly connections to Vienna, Graz and neighbouring Villach.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- Klagenfurt has daily connections to Graz departing close to the main train station and to Ljubljana in Slovenia. Tickets can be bought directly on the bus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Klagenfurt is located at the A-2 motorway and has four exits therefore it can be easily reached by Graz, Vienna and Villach. The B-91 connects Klagenfurt to Slovenia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - Most sights of interest can be easily reached by foot. Klagenfurt offers an extensive bus network. Hiring a bicycle is recommended for travelling to Klagenfurt&#39;s beach, on the shore of the Worthersee in the Western outskirts of the city. Bikes can be hired at Neuer Platz.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - EISSALON TUTTI FRUTTI, LOCATED AT BURGGASSE 23, 9020 - (FAMOUS FOR ICE-CREAM AND COFFEE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - RESTAURANT FAMIGLIA, LOCATED AT EHRENTALER STR. 35, 9020 - (FAMOUS FOR CHOCOLATE PANCAKES AND STUFFED POTATOES WITH VANILLA SAUCE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - JOHANN ERICH ORASCH, LOCATED AT ST., GEORGENER STR. 13, 9020 - (FAMOUS FOR FRIED CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - CAT&rsquo;N&rsquo;COFFEE &ndash; DAS KATZENCAFE, LOCATED AT PAULITSCHGASSE 9, 9020 - (FAMOUS FOR CAKES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(852, 19, 99, 1922, 'Graz', 'AUSTRIA', 'GRAZ', 'graz-2779671_640.jpg', 'graz-2779671_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Austria&#39;s second largest city, Graz lies on the River Mur and has long been a popular stopover for tourists. Highlights include exploring its many historical buildings, particularly in the Old Town with its numerous Baroque facades. Another big draw is the Schlossberg, a large hill that rises behind the picturesque town. While excavations reveal the area was settled as far back as 800 AD, the town was first mentioned in 1128, after which time it passed into the hands of the Habsburgs and soon after rose in importance as a place of trade and commerce. As a result of this abundance of historically significant buildings, Graz is today an important cultural centre that was added to the list of UNESCO World Heritage Sites in 1999. Graz is the birthplace of Hollywood legend Arnold Schwarzenegger and a fun little museum dedicated to his career is well worth a visit. Graz is one of the few major cities in Europe to have preserved an architectural heritage equal to its history. From the Middle Ages to the 18th century each era is represented by different buildings exemplifying artistic movements from Italy, northern Europe or the Danube regions. Nestled in the southern part of Austria, around an hour&rsquo;s drive from the Slovenian border, Graz is a beautiful city and the second largest behind Vienna. Settlements have been present in Graz since the early ages and it has been part of the Hapsburg Empire and closely linked with Slovenia. The city has a rich educational history with a prevalent university population and has also been residence too many well known figures including Nicolai Tesla, Arnold Schwarzenegger and Erwin Schrodinger. With a city centre full of old architecture influenced by renaissance artist, Graz has a certain style and elegance and together with its great list of things to do, make a perfect tourist location in Austria.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Austria&rsquo;s second largest city offers a large selection of accommodation options for every type of traveller. Outside of the city&rsquo;s core in the Lend district are more affordable lodgings. Roughly a ten minute walk to the Altstadt, this area provides an economical alternative while still keeping tourists close to the attractions. If willing to compromise on privacy, the best prices are in private accommodations in local homes. Often, this means sharing a bathroom with other guests and occasionally evens the home owners. All budget choices are outside the Old Town.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Graz airport Flughafen Graz also known as Thalerhof lies around 9 kms south of the city centre. Scheduled flights operate to Graz from Berlin, Dusseldorf, Frankfurt, Munich, Stuttgart, Vienna, Zurich, Istanbul.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- The main station Hauptbahnhof is on the western edge of the city centre, at the end of the Annenstrasse. Graz has frequent connections to Vienna Hbf with direct trains every hour. Connections to Salzburg and most other Austrian Cities and Munich are also reasonably frequent.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Graz does not have a dedicated bus terminal. Private and public operators all operate from separate terminals. Westbus, Regional Busses and Eurolines operate buses to Graz from Vienna, Berlin, Budapest, Prague and Bratislava.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - The A-9 runs north south through Graz, mostly via the 6 miles Plabutsch tunnel. The A-2 just south of the city runs east west. Vienna is 127 miles up the A-2 to the east. A just as fast but much more scenic alternative route to Vienna is via Bruck taking the S-6.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - Graz has an excellent tram service running through the Jakominiplatz where the different routes meet. Graz also has an excellent city bus network taking in the parts of Graz not serviced by trams. Many buses go through Jakominiplatz, Hauptbahnhof. Graz is a city of cyclists, featuring an excellent network of cycle paths. Due to this using a bike to get around is one of the best choices. Taxis are also available 24 hours a day.</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - BACKEREI SORGER &lsquo;ZUM WEINREBENBACKER&rsquo;, LOCATED AT BACKEREI SORGER, EGGENBERGER ALLEE 36 8020 - (FAMOUS FOR PASTRIES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - LANDHAUSKELLER, LOCATED AT SCHMIEDGASSE 9, 8010 - (FAMOUS FOR TAFELSPITZ IS A DISH MADE FROM &nbsp;BEEF, APPLES AND HORSERADISH)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - THOMAWIRT, LOCATED AT LEONHARDSTRABE 40-42, 8010 - (FAMOUS FOR PORK BURGER AND VEAL CHIPS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - DER STEIRER, LOCATED AT BELGIERGASSE 1, 8020 - (FAMOUS FOR NOODLE SOUP)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - DELIKATESSEN-FRANKOWITSCH, LOCATED AT STEMPFERGASSE 2, 8010 - (FAMOUS FOR SANDWICHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - KUNSTHAUSCAFE, LOCATED AT SUDTIROLER PL. 2, 8020 - (FAMOUS FOR EGGS BENEDICT IS A BREAKFAST DISH MADE FROM EGGS, MUFFIN, &nbsp;BACON AND HOLLANDAISE SAUCE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - KREBSENKELLER, LOCATED AT SACKSTRABE 12, 8010 - (FAMOUS FOR CRAYFISH SOUP WITH CRAB MEAT)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>8 - RESTAURANT CARL BY PHILIPP HAIGES, LOCATED AT OPERNRING 5A 1, 8010 - (FAMOUS FOR TORTELLINI IS ATYPE OF DUMPLING STUFFED WITH A MIX OF MEAT (PORK LOIN, PROSCIUTTO) OR CHEESE)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(853, 19, 99, 1923, 'Steyr', 'AUSTRIA', 'STEYR', 'river-1226235_640.jpg', 'river-1226235_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Steyr was once a rival to Vienna and has retained the role of an important economic centre from its glorious past. The town is situated at the confluence of rivers Steyr and Enns. It has a long history as a manufacturing centre and has given its name to several manufacturers headquartered there, such as Steyr Mannlicher, Steyr Tractor and Steyr Automobile. The old town, huddled at the foot of a hillock at the confluence of the Enns and Steyr, has retained its character and charm. The central Stadtplaz is its finest urban scheme, with handsome houses with balconies, towers, gables and arcaded courtyards. Steyr is a statutory city, located in the Austrian federal state of Upper Austria. It is the administrative capital, though not part of Steyr Land District. &nbsp;Steyr is Austria&rsquo;s 12th largest town and the 3rd largest in Upper Austria. It has a stable population of around 38100 and is listed as a statutory city. The city has a long history as a manufacturing centre and has given its name to several manufacturers headquartered there such as former Steyr Daimler Puch conglomerate and its successor Steyr Motors. The area has been settled since Celtic times and became part of the Roman Empire around 15th century BC. As with many towns in Austria, the influence of Habsburgs and Babenberg&rsquo;s is evident and Steyr has been conquered and ruled by both during its history. The two rivers that run through Steyr are a dominating feature of its divisions as are the various manufacturing industries that have sprung up here over the years. The wonderful old town and wealth of historic buildings, coupled with Upper Austria&rsquo;s stunning scenery make Steyr a great town to visit. Steyr is an ancient town with modern amenities, marketing its rich cultural and architectural heritage in tourism.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Steyr am Nationalpark offers a wide range of accommodation Hotels, inns, private rooms, holiday apartments, youth hostel and a camping site idyllically situated on the bank of the Enns River. From luxurious four star hotels to guesthouses and hostels, there&#39;s something for every taste. Many of the accommodations are family run and housed in historical buildings full of charm. Tourists can also have choices depending on the preferred location and for easy access to the major attractions a centrally located hotel or hostel is preferable.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The closest international airport is located in Linz about 50 kms from Steyr.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By train </strong>- There are daily trains passing through Steyr over Linz or St. Valentine and over Selztal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- There are regular buses to Steyr from Vienna, Salzburg and Graz.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around </strong>- Public transport with city buses or walking because Steyr is very small and most locations are in walking distance.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - RESTAURANT PIZZERIA ALDO, LOCATED AT WOLFERNSTRABE 17, 4400 - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - BUBURUZA EIS, LOCATED AT ENGE G. 16, 4400 - (FAMOUS FOR ICE-CREAM)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - FRANZ FERDINAND, LOCATED AT GLEINKER G. 1, 4400 - (FAMOUS FOR FISH DISHES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - FIDO&#39;S, LOCATED AT KARL-PUNZER-STRABE 15, 4400 - (FAMOUS FOR EGG NOODLES WITH GREEN SALAD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - CAFE BRUCKNER, LOCATED AT HARATZM&uuml;LLERSTRA&szlig;E 4, 4400 - (FAMOUS FOR COFFEE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - CAFE KONDITOREI SCHMIDT, LOCATED AT STADTPL. 1, 4400 - (FAMOUS FOR CAKE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - ARKADE CAFE, LOCATED AT BERTL-KONRAD-STRABE 2, 4400 - (FAMOUS FOR PASTRIES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(854, 19, 99, 1924, 'Bad Ischl', 'AUSTRIA', 'BAD ISCHL', 'bad-ischl-2658851_640.jpg', 'bad-ischl-2658851_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Set in the heart of the Salzkammergut, Bad Ischl was the Austrian spa resort where the splendour of Franz Joseph&#39;s reins left its greatest mark it was also, for 70 years, one of the most brilliant centres of fashionable life in Europe. The resort&#39;s parks and Biedermeier style public buildings are clustered in setting of densely wooded mountains. Today, relics from 19th century spa life still exist, such as the Zauner cafe. Many travellers used to think of Bad Ischl primarily as the town where Zauner&#39;s pastry shop is located, to which connoisseurs drove miles for the sake of a cup of coffee and a slice of Guglhupf, a lemon sponge cake studded with raisins and nuts. Pastry continues to be the best known drawing card of a community that symbolizes, more than any other place except Vienna itself, the Old Austria of resplendent uniforms and balls and waltzes and operettas. Although the centre is built up, the town is charmingly laid out on a peninsula between the Rivers Traun and Ischl. Bad Ischl was the place where Emperor Franz Josef chose to establish his summer court and it was here that he met and fell in love with his future empress, the troubled Sisi, though his mother had intended him for Sisi&#39;s elder sister. Today one can enjoy the same sort of pastries whipped cream that the emperor loved. Afterward, tourists can hasten off to the town&#39;s modern spa, one of the best known in Austria. Stroll along the shaded Esplanade, where the pampered and privileged of the 19th century loved to take their constitutionals, usually after a quick stop at the Trinkhalle, a spa pavilion in high 19th century Austrian style, still in the middle of town on Ferdinand Aubock Platz.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">In the grand old days, the aristocratic families of the region would welcome paying guests at their charming castles. Today most of those castles are very fine hotels. There are also luxurious lakeside resorts, small country inns, even guesthouses without private baths that will do everything to make visitors feel comfortable. Many hotels offer half board, with dinner in addition to buffet breakfast included in the price. Happily, these hotels do not put their breathtakingly beautiful natural surroundings on the bill.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - The nearest airport to Bad Ischl is Salzburg Airport in the city of Salzburg. It is located approximately 65 kms from Bad Ischl and provides flights to destinations throughout Europe.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Bad Ischl has a railway station that is operated by Austrian Federal Railways, the national railway system of Austria.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - There are a number of bus services that reach Bad Ischl from various Austrian cities including nearby Salzburg.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - Public transport like buses, trams, taxis and private cabs are there running throughout the city to get around. Local train services are also there for far away destinations. There are hundreds of kilometres of hiking trails in Bad Ischl.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - HELI&#39;S, LOCATED AT KURHAUSSTRABE 8A, 4820 - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - RESTAURANT SCHNITZELKAISER, LOCATED AT LEITENBERGERSTRABE 2, 4820 - (FAMOUS FOR BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - CHINA-RESTAURANT HAPPY DRAGON, LOCATED AT PFARRGASSE 2, 4820 - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN SALAD)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - K.U.K. HOFWIRT ZU ISCHL, LOCATED AT WIRERSTRABE 2, 4820 - {FAMOUS FOR GOULASH IS A TYPE OF STEW MADE FROM MEAT, NOODLES, VEGETABLES (ESPECIALLY POTATOES), PAPRIKA AND SPICES}</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - CAFE RAMSAUER, LOCATED AT KAISER-FRANZ-JOSEF-STRABE 8, 4820 - (FAMOUS FOR COFFEE AND PASTRIES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - KAFFEESIEDEREI IMMERVOLL, LOCATED AT KREUZPL. 25, 4820 - (FAMOUS FOR CAKES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - RESTAURANT SISSY, LOCATED AT PFARRGASSE 2, 4820 - (FAMOUS FOR SANDWICH)</strong></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(855, 19, 99, 1925, 'Villach', 'AUSTRIA', 'VILLACH', 'autumn-1229966_640.jpg', 'autumn-1229966_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Villach, the second largest town in the state of Carinthia and the seventh largest in Austria, lies near the frontiers with Italy and Slovenia in the heart of the country&#39;s mountainous south. Surrounded by spectacular mountain scenery the Villacher Alpe to the west and the Karawanken chain to the south, together with the Julian Alps to the rear the town attract many visitors on their way to the Carinthian lakes for their thermal springs. There was already a bridge and fortified camp here in Roman times, and by 1007, the town had passed into the control of the Bishops of Bamberg, eventually becoming part of Austria in 1759. Its location makes it the perfect spot from which to explore the spectacular Alpe Adria area, a designated bioregion encompassing parts of Austria, Italy and Slovenia. Villach has roots spanning back to the Neolithic period and also traces of Roman influence with remains being unearthed of many Roman Artefacts. Located in Southern Austria, Villach is only a short drive from the borders of both Slovenia and is surrounded by encapsulating countryside, sparkling lakes and beautiful Alpine mountain ranges all of this makes it an idyllic destination with a great variety of outdoor activities connected with the natural world. Often called the secret capital of Carinthia, Villach is the region&#39;s economic and cultural centre. The vast surrounding territory, which reaches as far as the lakes Faaker See and Ossiacher See, offers numerous possibilities for relaxtion and leisure activities. Warmbad, with its springs and thermal baths, which justify Villach&#39;s reputation as a spa town, should not be neglected either. Indulge in some photography at the Villacher Alpenstrasse and enjoy some soothing scenes of the mountain ranges or go on a short picnic at the beautiful Lake Faak.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">This Villach ski resort has something for all family and amateur skiers. Villach is a place with wonderful hotels and the most modern thermal spas of Austria. Featuring free Wi-Fi and a children&#39;s playground, hotels here offer pet friendly accommodation in Villach. The city of Villach also offers student dorms; however, most students rent private accommodation. The 5 star and 4 star superior hotels in Villach await its guest with style and comforts at the highest level.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Villach has no domestic or international airport. The nearest airport is Flughafen Airport in Klagenfurt located 40 kms away from Villach.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - Villach is a railway gateway within Austria, so trains go from virtually every bigger city. There are also direct connections to Munich, Zurich, Venice, Ljubljana, Zagreb and Belgrade.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - The Tauernautobahn A-10 from the north, the Sudautobahn A-2 from the east and the Karawankenautobahn A-11 from Slovenia connects Villach to rest of the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus </strong>- Villach Bus Terminal is a bus station in Villach with intercity connections to cities in Austria like Vienna and international bus connections to Croatia, Germany, Italy and three more European countries.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - Villach is a quite small town, so it is easy to get around on foot. Taxis can be found near the railway station and in the centre of the city near Hauptplatz. Federal buses go to the surrounding area from the local Busbahnhof bus terminal.</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - CHICKIS, LOCATED AT HAUPTPL. 19, 9500 - (FAMOUS FOR CHICKEN SOUP ANFD CHICKEN WINGS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - GELATERIA ITALIANA BY LUIS, LOCATED AT ITALIENER STR. 13, 9500 - (FAMOUS FOR ICE-CREAM)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - PIZZA AL TAGLIO DA COSIMO, LOCATED AT HANS-GASSER-PLATZ 3, 9500 - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - PANPERFOCACCIA, LOCATED AT LEDERERGASSE 19, 9500 - (FAMOUS FOR TIRAMISU IS A TYPE OF DESERT MADE FROM SAVOIARDI, EGG YOLKS, MASCARPONE, COCOA, COFFEE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - FINKENSTEINER NUDELFABRIK, LOCATED AT WARMBADERSTRABE 34, 9585 - (FAMOUS FOR PASTA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - VILLACHER BRAUHOF, LOCATED AT BAHNHOFSTRABE 8, 9500 - (FAMOUS FOR BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - RAINER, LOCATED AT OBERER KIRCHENPL. 5, 9500 - (FAMOUS FOR CAKES AND PASTRY)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>8 - KAFFEE KLEINFEIN, LOCATED AT LEDERERGASSE 17C, 9500 - (FAMOUS FOR COFFEE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>9 - KONIG KEBAP 27, LOCATED AT POSTGASSE 2, 9500 - {FAMOUS FOR BRATWURSTIS A TYPE OF SAUSAGE MADE FROM MEAT OF (VEAL, PORK OR BEEF)}</strong></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(856, 19, 99, 1926, 'Zell Am See', 'AUSTRIA', 'ZELL AM SEE', 'lake-1546725_640.jpg', 'lake-1546725_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Zell Am See, located in the state of Salzburg, is another well known tourist destination, famous for its mountains and lakes. Once governed by French troops back in the early 19th century, Zell am See has hosted several international skiing competitions. Off the ski slopes, one of its most famous attractions is the Romanesque St. Hippolyte&rsquo;s Church, with an elevated walkway that dates back to the early 16th century. Zell am See is also a good starting point for the Grossglockner Alpine Road, a panoramic road famous for its high alpine scenery. Surrounded by the breathtaking Salzburg Mountains Zell Am See is one of the most picturesque alpine cities in Austria. The region is a nature lover&#39;s paradise winter brings the opportunity to enjoy the 80 miles of local ski slopes, while the warmer summer months are perfect for swimming in the incredibly blue waters of the Zeller See or cycling along the tree lined paths by its shores. If looking for something more relaxing, it&#39;s easy to spend a pleasant afternoon wandering through the picturesque city centre which is studded with brightly, cozy cafes and excellent restaurants. Austria&rsquo;s quintessential Alpine lake town, Zell Am See hugs its eponymous cobalt blue waters right on the edge of the mighty Hohe Tauern ranges. From its enclave of fir clad ridges and snow mantled peaks, the spot has become a veritable outdoorsy paradise, drawing millions of adventure travellers each year with the promise of some of Austria&rsquo;s finest sailing, hiking, mountain biking, scenic driving and skiing, which takes place mainly on the icecaps of the Kitzsteinhorn above nearby Kaprun. And as if that&rsquo;s not enough, Zell Am See is also home to one seriously handsome centre of ice cream coloured chalets, while rhododendron and edelweiss bloom from the timber verandas and earthy eateries of Dreifaltigkeitsgasse.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">The choice of accommodation is big in Zell am See. Hotels, inns, guest houses, apartments, holiday homes or campsites all accommodations can be found here in Zell Am See. Zell am See offers a wide range of hotels from 3-Star to 4-Star Superior hotels. The wide range of holiday flats and apartments in the Zell Am See region offers comfort, facilities and practical design for families, groups of friends and self caterers. Affordable accommodation with plenty of comfort and maximum flexibility this is what the B&amp;B&rsquo;s in Zell am See offer. The farms of Zell Am See offer tranquillity and relaxation surrounded by an extraordinary landscape.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air </strong>- Salzburg Airport also known as WA Mozart is easy to reach for people who wish to visit Zell Am See. Salzburg Airport is roughly 80 kms away. A shuttle, taxi, small plane or train will take tourists straight to Zell am See.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train </strong>- The Zell am See train station is located in the centre of the city. Tourists can use OBB trains as they provide several direct connections between Salzburg and Zell Am See.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road </strong>- Zell am See is well connected to the local traffic network. Travelling by car can be the best experience as the journey would be a combination of driving with the breathtaking Alpine panorama. Zell am See is a 2.5 hrs drive away from Munich via motorway A-9 and 1.5 hrs drives away from Salzburg via A-12 Inntalautobahn motorway.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around </strong>- Within the city, the train stations are easy to find on any city map. The postbus is a convenient bus system that travels around the town and it can connect to neighbouring cities and attractions. Cruise is one of the best ways to enjoy the beauty of Zeller See Lake sitting on one of the town&rsquo;s comfortable ships. Tourists can explore all the nooks and crannies of the town simply by strolling along the paved path that stretches around the entire Zell Am See Lake.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - CUPSTAR, LOCATED AT BAHNHOFSTRABE 5A, 5700 - (FAMOUS FOR COFFEE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - BAKERY KONDITOREI-CAFE UNTERKOFLER GMBH., LOCATED AT KIRCHGASSE 2, 5700 - (FAMOUS FOR PASTRIES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - SHIRAZ RESTAURANT, LOCATED AT BRUCKER BUNDESSTRABE 96, 5700 - (FAMOUS FOR SOUP, KEBAB AND CHICKEN)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - RESTAURANT PIZZERIA KARIN MAISHOFEN, LOCATED AT MAISHOFEN - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA AND PASTA)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5 - THE BURGER FACTOR, &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LOCATED AT SALZMANNSTRABE 2, 5700 - (FAMOUS FOR BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6 - BAN THAI, LOCATED AT BRUCKER BUNDESSTRABE 39, 5700 - (FAMOUS FOR SOUP, FRIED RICE WITH VEGETABLES AND PANANG IS A TYPE OF CURRY MADE FROM PEPPERS, GALANGAL, LEMONGRASS, KAFFIR LIME ZEST, CORIANDER, CUMIN SEEDS, GARLIC, SHALLOT, SHRIMP PASTE, SALT AND PEANUTS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7 - AYDIN, LOCATED AT BRUCKER BUNDESSTRA&szlig;E 8, 5700 - (FAMOUS FOR TABBOULEH IS A TYPE OF SALAD MADE FROM PARSLEY, TOMATO, BULGUR)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>8 - CAFE KONDITOREI MOSSHAMMER, LOCATED AT STADTPL. 4, 5700 - (FAMOUS FOR CHOCOLATE CAKE)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', ''),
(857, 19, 99, 1927, 'Kufstein', 'AUSTRIA', 'KUFSTEIN', 'fortress-1618116_640.jpg', 'fortress-1618116_6401.jpg', '<p style="text-align:justify">Known as the pearl of Tyrol, the town of Kufstein features about 15000 inhabitants. This locality has already been celebrated in a song of 1947, which praises Kufstein to be a calm place located along the Inn River. Kufstein is a pretty little medieval town located in the Tyrolian Alps on the Inn River. It is the second largest town in Tyrol only the capital Innsbruck is bigger. One of the town&rsquo;s best known attractions is the imposing Kufstein Fortress, which dates back to the 13th century and sits high above the city. The fortress is also home to the Heldenorgel organ, which is the world&rsquo;s largest outdoor organ. While in this town, make sure to stroll down the Romerhofgasse, an enchanting lane in central Kufstein that might makes feel as if the setting for a fairy tale. The old Tirolese border town of Kufstein is a popular holiday spot boasting attractive lake scenery and good walking and climbing in the Kaisergebirge. A stroll through the town is very rewarding, taking past the remains of old walls and moated towers, pleasant squares with their fountains and monuments and many historical buildings. The town itself lies on the river Inn and is surrounded by the Northern Limestone Alps and edges onto the Bavarian Alpine Foreland. Settlements and human presence has been dated as far back as the Stone Age, and also traces of the Roman Empire have been found. In later history, Kufstein saw many different rulers owing to its important position and the large fortress that remains an important part of the town&rsquo;s culture today. With a traditional Austrian feel and such beautiful streets as the Romerhofgasse, coupled together with the multitude of outdoor activities, Kufstein is a true tourist gem. To enjoy a view of the outstanding site, climb the wooded rise of the Heldenhugel. The nearby Kaisergebirge have helped the town in becoming an attractive tourist destination and can be quickly accessed by chair lift.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify">Enjoy a relaxing stay at charming Kufstein hotels on Austria&#39;s Inn River banks as there are lot of options vailable for accommodation in Kufstein. The modern and yet tradition conscious hotels are located directly in the centre of Kufstein. Kufstein is an all year round holiday region that boast some great scenery and a number of budgets, mid range and superior hotels.</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Air</strong> - Kufstein does not have airport. The nearest airport is Kranebitten Airport in Innsbruck located about 75 kms away from the town of Kufstein.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Train</strong> - There are good connections from both Munich and Innsbruck to Kufsteinerland . By train, tourists will arrive directly at the OBB and DB station in Kufstein.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Bus</strong> - Kufstein has ideal bus connections to all parts of the region and many landlords also gladly pick up their guests directly at the station.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>By Road</strong> - Kufstein is connected to major cities like Innsbruck, Vienna, Sqalzburg, Munich etc via Motorways A-8, A-93, A-12, A-1 and A-22.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Getting Around</strong> - There are local trains and buses to travel around the city. Private cabs and taxi services are also available here. Kufstein is a small town, hence walking around the town is also an option.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<blockquote>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1 - RESTAURANT PURLEPAUS, LOCATED AT UNTERER STADTPL. 18, 6330 - (FAMOUS FOR TARTE FLAMBEE IS A TYPE OF DISH MADE FROM BREAD DOUGH, FROMAGE FRAIS OR CREME FRAICHE, ONIONS, LARDONS)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2 - KAFFEEHAUS DIE BOHNE TIROLS, LOCATED AT KINKSTRABE 30, 6330 - (FAMOUS FOR COFFEE, PASTRIES AND CAKES)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>3 - HANS IM GLUCK - BURGERGRILL, LOCATED AT UNTERER STADTPL. 2, 6330 - (FAMOUS FOR BURGER)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4 - JOLLY PIZZERIA RESTAURANT MILCO RASO, LOCATED AT ANTON KARG-STRABE 19, 6330 - (FAMOUS FOR PIZZA)</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', '');
